window.ICML_PAPERS["68685"] = [{"id":"66738","en":"StepCodeReasoner: Aligning Code Reasoning with Stepwise Execution Traces via Reinforcement Learning","ko":"StepCodeReasoner: 강화학습을 통해 단계별 실행 트레이스와 코드 추론을 정렬","authors":"Hao Wang, Lei Sha, Jie Zhang","pos":"#125","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=0vTONq9Z8j","abs":"<p>Existing code reasoning methods primarily supervise final code outputs, ignoring intermediate states, often leading to reward hacking where correct answers are obtained through inconsistent reasoning. We propose StepCodeReasoner, a framework that introduces explicit intermediate execution-state supervision. By automatically inserting structured print-based execution-trace anchors into code, the model is trained to predict runtime states at each step, transforming code reasoning into a verifiable, stepwise execution modeling problem. Building on this execution-aware method, we introduce Bi-Level GRPO}, a reinforcement learning algorithm for structured credit assignment at two levels: inter-trajectory, comparing alternative execution paths, and intra-trajectory, rewarding intermediate accuracy based on its impact on downstream correctness. Extensive experiments demonstrate that StepCodeReasoner achieves SOTA performance in code reasoning.  In particular, our 7B model achieves 91.1\\% on CRUXEval and 86.5\\% on LiveCodeBench, outperforming the CodeReasoner-7B baseline (86.0\\% and 77.7\\%) and GPT-4o (85.6\\% and 75.1\\%). Furthermore, on the execution-trace benchmark REval, our model scores 82.9\\%, outperforming baseline CodeReasoner-7B (72.3\\%), its 14B counterpart (81.1\\%), and GPT-4o (77.3\\%). Additionally, our approach also improves code generation performance, demonstrating that explicit execution modeling enhances both code reasoning and code generation.</p>"},{"id":"62570","en":"Ubiquity of Homeostatic Hebbian Dynamics in Regularized Learning","ko":"규제 학습에서 Homeostatic Hebbian Dynamics의 보편성","authors":"David Koplow, Tomaso A Poggio, Liu Ziyin","pos":"#1301","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=fSRmJOzMA1","abs":"<p>Hebbian and anti-Hebbian plasticity are widely observed in the brain and are classically modeled as mechanistic, local homosynaptic rules stabilized by homeostatic constraints. This raises an identifiability question: does observing Hebbian/anti-Hebbian structure in synaptic updates uniquely imply an underlying Hebbian computation? We identify an alternative, emergent route. We show that near stationarity, L2 weight decay generically drives the \\emph{learning-signal} component of many update rules to align with a Hebbian direction, with alignment increasing monotonically with decay strength. This Hebbian-like signature is not specific to SGD and can arise even for non-learning or random update rules long before learning has ceased. We further show that stochastic perturbations can induce anti-Hebbian alignment, yielding a simple tradeoff with weight decay and a phase boundary in regression settings. These mechanisms do not replace standard Hebbian theory; they can coexist with genuine Hebbian plasticity and complicate the interpretation of synaptic measurements, motivating experiments that distinguish mechanistic Hebbian computation from emergent Hebbian signatures.</p>","absKo":"<p>Hebbian 및 anti-Hebbian plasticity는 뇌에서 널리 관찰되며, 고전적으로 homeostatic constraint에 의해 안정화되는 기계론적이고 local한 homosynaptic rule로 모델링된다. 이는 식별 가능성의 질문을 제기한다: synaptic update에서 Hebbian/anti-Hebbian 구조를 관찰하는 것이 반드시 underlying Hebbian computation을 uniquely 함의하는가? 우리는 대안적인 emergent 경로를 식별한다. 정상 상태에 가까워지면, L2 weight decay는 다양한 update rule의 \\emph{learning-signal} 성분이 Hebbian 방향과 정렬되도록 일반적으로 유도하며, 이러한 정렬은 decay strength가 증가할수록 단조롭게 커진다. 이 Hebbian-like signature는 SGD에만 특이적인 것이 아니며, 학습이 아직 끝나기 훨씬 전에도 비학습적이거나 무작위인 update rule에서조차 나타날 수 있다. 또한 stochastic perturbation이 anti-Hebbian 정렬을 유도할 수 있음을 보이며, regression setting에서 weight decay와의 간단한 tradeoff 및 phase boundary를 도출한다. 이러한 메커니즘은 표준 Hebbian theory를 대체하지 않는다. 오히려 진정한 Hebbian plasticity와 공존할 수 있으며 synaptic measurement의 해석을 더 복잡하게 만든다. 이는 기계론적 Hebbian computation과 emergent Hebbian signature를 구분하는 실험의 필요성을 뒷받침한다.</p>"},{"id":"68819","en":"Reasoning-Driven Synthetic Data Generation and Evaluation","ko":"추론 주도 합성 데이터 생성 및 평가","authors":"Tim Davidson, Benoit Seguin, Enrico Bacis, Cesar Ilharco, Hamza Harkous","pos":"#1814","abs":"<p>Although many AI applications of interest require specialized multi-modal models, relevant data to train such models is inherently scarce or inaccessible. Filling these gaps with human annotators is prohibitively expensive, error-prone, and time-consuming, leading model builders to increasingly consider synthetic data as a scalable alternative. However, existing synthetic data generation methods often rely on manual prompts, evolutionary algorithms, or extensive seed data from the target distribution — limiting their scalability, explainability, and control. In this paper, we introduce Simula: a novel reasoning-driven framework for data generation and evaluation. It employs a seedless, agentic approach to generate synthetic datasets at scale, allowing users to define desired dataset characteristics through an explainable and controllable process that enables fine-grained resource allocation. We show the efficacy of our approach on a variety of datasets, rigorously testing both intrinsic and downstream properties. Our work (1) offers guidelines for synthetic data mechanism design, (2) provides insights into generating and evaluating synthetic data at scale, and (3) unlocks new opportunities for developing and deploying AI in domains where data scarcity or privacy concerns are paramount.</p>"},{"id":"62734","en":"Learning GUI Grounding with Spatial Reasoning from Visual Feedback","ko":"시각 피드백을 통한 Spatial Reasoning 기반 GUI Grounding 학습","authors":"Yu Zhao, Wei-Ning Chen, Huseyin Inan, Samuel Kessler, Lu Wang, Lukas Wutschitz, Fangkai Yang, Chaoyun Zhang, Pasquale Minervini, Saravanakumar Rajmohan, Robert A Sim","pos":"#2013","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=dqmt0Yd4rc","abs":"<p>Graphical User Interface (GUI) grounding is commonly framed as a coordinate prediction task – given a natural language instruction, generate on-screen coordinates for actions such as clicks and keystrokes. However, recent Vision Language Models (VLMs) often fail to predict accurate numeric coordinates when processing GUI images with high resolutions and complex layouts. To address this issue, we reframe GUI grounding as an interactive search task, where the VLM generates actions to move a cursor in the GUI to locate UI elements. At each step, the model determines the target object, evaluates the spatial relations between the cursor and the target, and moves the cursor closer to the target conditioned on the movement history. In this interactive process, the rendered cursor provides visual feedback to help the model align its predictions with the corresponding on-screen locations. We train our GUI grounding model, GUI-Cursor, using multi-step online reinforcement learning with a dense trajectory-based reward function. Experimental results demonstrate that GUI-Cursor surpasses strong baselines in GUI grounding and agentic tasks, achieving superior performance with the same base models while requiring less training data. Further analysis shows that GUI-Cursor learns to adaptively conduct more steps on more difficult examples, and it obtains better spatial reasoning capability on out-of-distribution domains.</p>","absKo":"<p>Graphical User Interface (GUI) grounding은 일반적으로 coordinate prediction task로 프레이밍된다. 즉, 자연어 지시가 주어졌을 때 클릭이나 keystroke 같은 동작을 위한 화면 좌표를 생성하는 것이다. 그러나 최근 Vision Language Model (VLM)은 고해상도와 복잡한 layout을 가진 GUI image를 처리할 때 정확한 numeric coordinate를 예측하는 데 자주 실패한다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 GUI grounding을 interactive search task로 재구성한다. 이때 VLM은 GUI에서 cursor를 이동시켜 UI element를 찾기 위한 action을 생성한다. 각 step에서 model은 target object를 결정하고, cursor와 target 간의 spatial relation을 평가하며, movement history를 조건으로 cursor를 target에 더 가깝게 이동시킨다. 이러한 interactive process에서 렌더링된 cursor는 시각적 feedback을 제공하여 model이 예측을 해당 화면 위치와 맞추도록 돕는다. 우리는 dense trajectory-based reward function을 사용하는 multi-step online reinforcement learning으로 GUI grounding model인 GUI-Cursor를 학습한다. 실험 결과, GUI-Cursor는 GUI grounding 및 agentic task에서 강력한 baseline을 능가하며, 더 적은 training data로 같은 base model에서 우수한 성능을 달성한다. 추가 분석은 GUI-Cursor가 더 어려운 예제에서 적응적으로 더 많은 step을 수행하는 법을 학습하며, out-of-distribution domain에서 더 나은 spatial reasoning capability를 획득함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"65694","en":"Enhancing Neural Theorem Proving via High-Quality Proof Selection and Verifier Feedback","ko":"고품질 증명 선택과 검증기 피드백을 통한 신경 정리 증명 강화","authors":"Xiaoxue Zhu, Jilin Hu, Fuyuan Zhang, Jianyu Zhang, Yongwang Zhao","pos":"#2102","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=B61SpkriNe","abs":"<p>Recent advances in large language models have accelerated neural theorem proving (NTP). Isabelle is a mature and important formal theorem prover that has been widely used in software and hardware verification. However, progress in the Isabelle setting remains limited. Existing approaches either optimize search strategies or train on highly imbalanced raw proof corpora. At the same time, the specialized structure of Isabelle proofs limits the effectiveness of general-purpose data selection methods. To address these challenges, we adopt a data-centric framework for neural theorem proving in Isabelle. We characterize high-quality formal proof data along three complementary dimensions—proof complexity, semantic coverage, and reasoning diversity (PSR)—and propose a PSR-guided data selection pipeline to construct a compact, high-quality training subset. In addition, we leverage verifier feedback as a dynamic data signal during inference, introducing a dynamic feedback-based prompt optimization that iteratively incorporates Isabelle verifier feedback to guide proof generation. We construct and release a 4k high-quality Isabelle dataset based on the PSR criterion. On the miniF2F-test, fine-tuning solely on PSR-selected data achieves 84.8% Pass@64. When further combined with dynamic feedback–based prompt optimization, the full framework improves performance to 90.6% Pass@64, establishing a new state of the art for neural theorem proving in Isabelle.</p>"},{"id":"63029","en":"Closing the Loop: Universal Repository Representation with RPG-Encoder","ko":"루프 닫기: RPG-Encoder를 활용한 범용 저장소 표현","authors":"Jane Luo, Chengyu Yin, Xin Zhang, Qingtao Li, Steven Liu, Yiming Huang, Jie Wu, Hao Liu, Yangyu Huang, Yu Kang, Fangkai Yang, Ying Xin, Scarlett Li","pos":"#2214","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=am8FJ31GWi","abs":"<p>Current repository agents encounter a reasoning disconnect due to fragmented representations, as existing methods rely on isolated API documentation or dependency graphs that lack semantic depth. We consider repository comprehension and generation to be inverse processes within a unified cycle: generation expands intent into implementation, while comprehension compresses implementation back into intent. To address this, we propose RPG-Encoder, a framework that generalizes the Repository Planning Graph (RPG) from a static generative blueprint into a unified, high-fidelity representation. RPG-Encoder closes the reasoning loop through three mechanisms: (1) Encoding raw code into the RPG that combines lifted semantic features with code dependencies; (2) Evolving the topology incrementally to decouple maintenance costs from repository scale, reducing overhead by 95.7%; and (3) Operating as a unified interface for structure-aware navigation. In evaluations, RPG-Encoder establishes state-of-the-art repository understanding on SWE-bench Verified with 93.7% Acc@5 and exceeds the best baseline by over 10% on SWE-bench Live. These results highlight our superior fine-grained localization accuracy in complex codebases. Furthermore, it achieves 98.5% reconstruction coverage on RepoCraft, confirming RPG's high-fidelity capacity to mirror the original codebase and closing the loop between intent and implementation.</p>","absKo":"<p>현재 repository agent는 분절된 representation 때문에 reasoning disconnect를 겪는다. 기존 방법이 의미적 깊이가 부족한 고립된 API 문서나 dependency graph에 의존하기 때문이다. 우리는 repository comprehension과 generation을 하나의 통합된 cycle 내에서 서로 역연산인 과정으로 본다. 즉, generation은 intent를 implementation으로 확장하고, comprehension은 implementation을 다시 intent로 압축한다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 Repository Planning Graph(RPG)를 정적 generative blueprint에서 통합된 고충실도 representation으로 일반화한 framework, RPG-Encoder를 제안한다. RPG-Encoder는 세 가지 메커니즘을 통해 reasoning loop를 닫는다: (1) raw code를 lifted semantic feature와 code dependency를 결합한 RPG로 인코딩하고, (2) topology를 점진적으로 진화시켜 유지보수 비용을 repository 규모와 분리함으로써 오버헤드를 95.7% 줄이며, (3) structure-aware navigation을 위한 통합 인터페이스로 작동한다. 평가에서 RPG-Encoder는 SWE-bench Verified에서 93.7% Acc@5로 state-of-the-art repository understanding을 달성하고, SWE-bench Live에서는 최고의 baseline을 10% 이상 능가한다. 이러한 결과는 복잡한 codebase에서 뛰어난 fine-grained localization 정확도를 보여준다. 더 나아가 RepoCraft에서 98.5% reconstruction coverage를 달성하여 RPG가 원본 codebase를 높은 충실도로 반영하고 intent와 implementation 사이의 loop를 닫는 능력을 확인한다.</p>"},{"id":"67124","en":"Position: It is Time to Virtualize Foundation Models with a Self-evolving Operating System Layer","ko":"Position: 이제 자기 진화형 운영체제 계층으로 Foundation Model을 가상화할 때이다","authors":"Suparna Bhattacharya, Tarun Kumar, Cong Xu, Satish Mopur, Jiahao Li, Ashish Mishra, Aalap Tripathy, ANNMARY KOOMTHANAM, Martin Foltin, Ian Foster","pos":"#2714","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=bVdfIOoU5g","abs":"<p>AI applications have shifted from single, mono-lithic foundation models (FM) to compound agentic systems. Yet today’s stacks remain fragmented: even as protocols (e.g., MCP, A2A) ease tool/agent connectivity, each framework embeds an implicit runtime for state, memory, budgets, and guardrails, making behavior non-portable and governance brittle. It mirrors computing before operating systems, when every program re-implemented basic services. This position paper argues that the field now needs a Foundation Model Operating System (FMOS): a system layer that virtualizes FM interactions analogous to how virtual machines abstract physical hardware, giving applications the illusion of dedicated, trustworthy FM instances with effectively unbounded capabilities. Internally, the FMOS orchestrates knowledge across memory tiers, model selection and resource allocation, and verification and policy enforcement. Like the human brain switching between fast intuition and slow deliberation, the FMOS learns when to intervene and when to let inference proceed directly and continuously adapting its policies based on operational experience.</p>"},{"id":"61514","en":"SWE-Perf: Can Language Models Optimize Code Performance on Real-World Repositories?","ko":"SWE-Perf: Language Models는 실제 Repository에서 코드 성능을 최적화할 수 있는가?","authors":"Xinyi He, Qian Liu, Mingzhe Du, Lin Yan, ZhiJie Fan, Yiming Huang, Yin Zheng, Zejian Yuan, Zejun MA","pos":"#3315","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=pNxw4i5Dp2","abs":"<p>Code performance optimization is paramount in real-world software engineering and critical for production-level systems. While Large Language Models (LLMs) have demonstrated impressive capabilities in code generation and bug fixing, their proficiency in enhancing code performance at the repository level remains largely unexplored. To address this gap, we introduce SWE-Perf, the first benchmark specifically designed to systematically evaluate LLMs on code performance optimization tasks within authentic repository contexts. SWE-Perf comprises 140 carefully curated instances, each derived from performance-improving pull requests from popular GitHub repositories. Each benchmark instance includes the relevant codebase, target functions, performance-related tests, expert-authored patches, and executable environments. Through a comprehensive evaluation of representative methods that span file-level and repo-level approaches (e.g., Agentless and OpenHands), we reveal a substantial capability gap between existing LLMs and expert-level optimization performance, highlighting critical research opportunities in this emerging field.</p>","absKo":"<p>Code performance optimization은 실제 software engineering에서 무엇보다 중요하며 production-level system에 필수적이다. Large Language Model(LLM)은 code generation과 bug fixing에서 인상적인 능력을 보여 왔지만, repository 수준에서 code performance를 향상시키는 능력은 아직 충분히 탐구되지 않았다. 이 공백을 메우기 위해, 우리는 실제 repository context 내에서 LLM의 code performance optimization task를 체계적으로 평가하도록 특별히 설계된 첫 benchmark인 SWE-Perf를 소개한다. SWE-Perf는 세심하게 선별된 140개의 instance로 구성되며, 각 instance는 인기 있는 GitHub repository의 performance-improving pull request에서 파생된다. 각 benchmark instance는 관련 codebase, target function, performance-related test, expert가 작성한 patch, 그리고 실행 가능한 environment를 포함한다. File-level과 repo-level approach를 아우르는 대표적 방법들(예: Agentless와 OpenHands)에 대한 포괄적 평가를 통해, 우리는 기존 LLM과 expert-level optimization performance 사이에 상당한 능력 격차가 있음을 밝히며, 이 emerging field에서 중요한 연구 기회를 강조한다.</p>"},{"id":"62319","en":"Beyond Theorem Proving: Formulation, Framework and Benchmark for Formal Problem-Solving","ko":"정리 증명을 넘어: Formal Problem-Solving를 위한 Formulation, Framework, Benchmark","authors":"Qi Liu, Xinhao Zheng, Renqiu Xia, Xingzhi Qi, Qinxiang Cao, Junchi Yan","pos":"#3400","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=hgMZraPlSv","abs":"<p>Large language models (LLMs) have achieved remarkable progress in mathematical reasoning, yet persistently suffer from hallucinations and erroneous logic. While formal theorem proving (FTP) shows promise in process-level reliability, it is limited to <em>verification</em> (checking known propositions). This leaves constructive problem-solving (finding unknown terms that satisfy specific conditions) underexplored and disconnected from process-level verifiability. To bridge this gap, we introduce <strong>FPS</strong> (<em><strong>F</strong>ormal <strong>P</strong>roblem-<strong>S</strong>olving</em>), a principled framework to encompass the end-to-end problem-solving process in Lean 4. In FPS, the answer is an unknown metavariable coupled with a proof obligation, forcing it to be mathematically derived and verified. We further present <strong>D-FPS</strong> (<em><strong>D</strong>eductive <strong>FPS</strong></em>), which enforces a rigorous chain-of-thought structure, aligning formal derivation with human reasoning steps. To support this direction, we construct three benchmarks via the manual refactoring of over 1,000 problems: <strong>FormalMath500</strong>, <strong>MiniF2F-Solving</strong>, and <strong>PutnamBench-Solving</strong>. We further propose <strong>RPE</strong> (<em><strong>R</strong>estricted <strong>P</strong>ropositional <strong>E</strong>quivalence</em>), a symbolic metric that evaluates semantic correctness beyond brittle string matching. Extensive experiments with state-of-the-art provers reveal that solving is significantly harder than proving, highlighting the ``alignment tax'' required to transition from loose validity checking to constructive, human-aligned reasoning.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large language model (LLM)은 수학적 추론에서 놀라운 진전을 이루었지만, hallucination과 잘못된 논리로부터 지속적으로 어려움을 겪고 있다. formal theorem proving (FTP)은 process-level 신뢰성 측면에서 가능성을 보이지만, <em>verification</em>(알려진 명제를 검증하는 일)에 한정된다. 이로 인해 constructive problem-solving(특정 조건을 만족하는 미지의 항을 찾는 일)은 충분히 탐구되지 못했고, process-level verifiability와도 분리되어 있었다. 이 격차를 메우기 위해, 우리는 Lean 4에서 end-to-end problem-solving 과정을 포괄하는 원칙적 framework인 <strong>FPS</strong>(<em><strong>F</strong>ormal <strong>P</strong>roblem-<strong>S</strong>olving</em>)를 도입한다. FPS에서는 답이 proof obligation과 결합된 unknown metavariable이므로, 수학적으로 도출되고 검증되도록 강제된다. 또한 우리는 엄격한 chain-of-thought 구조를 강제하여 formal derivation을 인간의 추론 단계와 정렬시키는 <strong>D-FPS</strong>(<em><strong>D</strong>eductive <strong>FPS</strong></em>)를 제시한다. 이 방향을 지원하기 위해, 1,000개가 넘는 문제를 수작업으로 refactoring하여 세 개의 benchmark, 즉 <strong>FormalMath500</strong>, <strong>MiniF2F-Solving</strong>, <strong>PutnamBench-Solving</strong>을 구축한다. 더 나아가, brittle한 string matching을 넘어 semantic correctness를 평가하는 symbolic metric인 <strong>RPE</strong>(<em><strong>R</strong>estricted <strong>P</strong>ropositional <strong>E</strong>quivalence</em>)를 제안한다. state-of-the-art prover를 사용한 광범위한 실험은 solving이 proving보다 상당히 더 어렵다는 점을 보여주며, 느슨한 validity checking에서 구성적이고 인간 정렬적인 추론으로 전환하는 데 필요한 ``alignment tax''를 부각한다.</p>"},{"id":"62161","en":"AutoWebWorld: Synthesizing Infinite Verifiable Web Environments via Finite State Machines","ko":"AutoWebWorld: 유한 상태 기계로 무한한 검증 가능한 웹 환경 합성","authors":"Yifan WU, Yiran Peng, Yiyu Chen, Jianhao Ruan, Zijie Zhuang, Cheng Yang, Jiayi Zhang, Man CHEN, Yenchi Tseng, Zhaoyang Yu, Liang Chen, Yuyao Zhai, Bang Liu, Chenglin Wu, Yuyu Luo","pos":"#3402","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=jBPFdqmOck","abs":"<p>The performance of autonomous Web GUI agents heavily relies on the quality and quantity of their training data. However, a fundamental bottleneck persists: collecting interaction trajectories from real-world websites is expensive and difficult to verify. The underlying state transitions are hidden, leading to reliance on inconsistent and costly external verifiers (e.g., human or LLM judges) to evaluate step-level correctness. To address this, we propose AutoWebWorld, a novel framework for synthesizing controllable and verifiable web environments by modeling them as Finite State Machines (FSMs) and use coding agents to translate FSMs into interactive websites. Unlike real websites, where state transitions are implicit, AutoWebWorld explicitly defines all states, actions, and transition rules. This enables programmatic verification: action correctness is checked against predefined rules, and task success is confirmed by reaching a goal state in the FSM graph. AutoWebWorld enables a fully automated search-and-verify pipeline, generating over 11,663 verified trajectories from 29 diverse web environments at only \\$0.04 per trajectory. Training on this synthetic data significantly boosts real-world performance. Our 7B Web GUI agent achieves state-of-the-art on WebVoyager, outperforming all baselines within 15 steps. Furthermore, we observe a clear scaling law: as the synthetic data volume increases, performance on WebVoyager and Online-Mind2Web consistently improves.</p>","absKo":"<p>autonomous Web GUI agent의 성능은 학습 데이터의 품질과 양에 크게 좌우된다. 그러나 근본적인 병목은 여전히 남아 있다. 실제 웹사이트에서 interaction trajectory를 수집하는 일은 비용이 많이 들고 검증도 어렵다. underlying state transition은 숨겨져 있어, step-level correctness를 평가하기 위해 일관성이 떨어지고 비용이 큰 외부 verifier(예: human 또는 LLM judge)에 의존하게 된다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 웹 환경을 Finite State Machine(FSM)으로 모델링하고 coding agent를 사용해 FSM을 interactive website로 변환함으로써 제어 가능하고 검증 가능한 web environment를 합성하는 새로운 framework인 AutoWebWorld를 제안한다. state transition이 암묵적인 실제 웹사이트와 달리, AutoWebWorld는 모든 state, action, transition rule을 명시적으로 정의한다. 이를 통해 programmatic verification이 가능해진다. action correctness는 미리 정의된 rule과 대조하여 검사되고, task success는 FSM graph에서 goal state에 도달했는지로 확인된다. AutoWebWorld는 완전 자동화된 search-and-verify pipeline을 가능하게 하며, 29개의 다양한 web environment에서 검증된 trajectory 11,663개 이상을 trajectory당 \\$0.04의 비용으로 생성한다. 이 합성 데이터로 학습하면 실제 환경 성능이 크게 향상된다. 우리의 7B Web GUI agent는 WebVoyager에서 state-of-the-art를 달성하며, 15 step 이내에서 모든 baseline을 능가한다. 또한 합성 데이터의 양이 증가할수록 WebVoyager와 Online-Mind2Web 성능이 일관되게 향상되는 명확한 scaling law도 관찰된다.</p>"},{"id":"63704","en":"Learning Dynamics of Zeroth-Order Optimization: A Kernel Perspective","ko":"Zeroth-Order Optimization의 학습 역학: 커널 관점","authors":"Zhe Li, Bicheng Ying, Zidong Liu, Haibo Yang","pos":"#3600","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=UTIylOfVUb","abs":"<p>Classical optimization theory establishes that zeroth-order (ZO) algorithms suffer from a dimension-dependent slowdown, with convergence rates typically scaling with the model dimension compared to first-order methods.      However, in contrast to these theoretical expectations, a growing body of recent work demonstrates the successful application of ZO methods to fine-tuning Large Language Models (LLMs) with billions of parameters.     To explain this paradox, we derive the one-step learning dynamics of ZO SGD, where the empirical Neural Tangent Kernel (eNTK) naturally emerges as the key term governing the learning behavior.     Inspection of the eNTK produced by ZO-SGD reveals that each element corresponds to the inner product of neural tangent vectors projected onto a random low-dimensional subspace.      Thus, by invoking the Johnson-Lindenstrauss Lemma, our analysis shows that the fidelity of the ZO eNTK is governed primarily by the number of perturbations.     Crucially, the approximation error depends on the model output size rather than the massive parameter dimension.      This dimension-free property provides a theoretical justification for the scalability of ZO methods to LLMs finetuning tasks.      We believe that this kernel-based framework offers a novel perspective for understanding ZO methods within the context of learning dynamics.</p>","absKo":"<p>Classical optimization theory는 zeroth-order(ZO) algorithm이 dimension-dependent slowdown을 겪으며, convergence rate가 보통 first-order method에 비해 model dimension에 따라 스케일된다고 확립해 왔다. 그러나 이러한 이론적 기대와 달리, 최근의 growing body of work는 수십억 개의 parameter를 가진 Large Language Model(LLM) fine-tuning에 ZO method를 성공적으로 적용했음을 보여 준다. 이 역설을 설명하기 위해 우리는 ZO SGD의 one-step learning dynamics를 유도하고, empirical Neural Tangent Kernel(eNTK)이 learning behavior를 지배하는 핵심 항으로 자연스럽게 등장함을 보인다. ZO-SGD가 생성하는 eNTK를 살펴보면, 각 element는 random low-dimensional subspace에 투영된 neural tangent vector의 inner product에 해당한다. 따라서 Johnson-Lindenstrauss Lemma를 적용하면, 우리의 분석은 ZO eNTK의 fidelity가 주로 perturbation 수에 의해 결정됨을 보인다. 결정적으로 approximation error는 massive한 parameter dimension이 아니라 model output size에 의존한다. 이러한 dimension-free 성질은 LLM finetuning task에 ZO method가 확장 가능하다는 이론적 근거를 제공한다. 우리는 이 kernel-based framework가 learning dynamics 맥락에서 ZO method를 이해하기 위한 새로운 관점을 제공한다고 믿는다.</p>"},{"id":"64351","en":"Asymmetric Multi-View Clustering with Hyperbolic Uncertainty Modeling","ko":"쌍곡 불확실성 모델링을 이용한 비대칭 다중 시점 클러스터링","authors":"Yiming Wang, Qun Li, Dongxia Chang, Jie Wen, Hua Dai, Fu Xiao","pos":"#3917","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=OTKdKRLXf7","abs":"<p>Deep Multi-View Clustering (MVC) aims to extract a unified semantic consensus from diverse data sources without supervision. However, current approaches relying on flat Euclidean embeddings often fail to model data uncertainty, resulting in rigid alignment where high-quality views are forced to drift toward corrupted ones. To address these challenges, we propose the Hyperbolic Asymmetric Multi-view Clustering (HAMC) framework. By embedding features into the Poincaré ball model, HAMC leverages the exponential volume growth of hyperbolic geometry to optimize cluster separability. It pushes high-confidence representations toward the boundary while retaining noisy ones near the origin. To mitigate noise, we introduce an asymmetric view alignment mechanism, enabling reliable views to unidirectionally guide unreliable ones. Furthermore, a consensus-aware cluster learning strategy is designed to construct robust global pseudo-labels via a confidence-based screening scheme, refining the cluster structure. Extensive experiments against 13 baselines demonstrate that HAMC achieves state-of-the-art performance.</p>","absKo":"<p>Deep Multi-View Clustering(MVC)은 감독 없이 다양한 데이터 소스에서 통합된 semantic consensus를 추출하는 것을 목표로 합니다. 그러나 현재의 flat Euclidean embedding에 의존하는 접근법은 데이터 불확실성을 모델링하는 데 실패하는 경우가 많아, 고품질 view가 손상된 view 쪽으로 억지로 이동하는 경직된 정렬을 초래합니다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해 우리는 Hyperbolic Asymmetric Multi-view Clustering(HAMC) framework를 제안합니다. 특징을 Poincaré ball model에 임베딩함으로써, HAMC는 hyperbolic geometry의 지수적 부피 증가를 활용해 cluster separability를 최적화합니다. 이 방법은 높은 신뢰도의 representation을 경계(boundary) 쪽으로 밀어내는 동시에, 노이즈가 큰 representation은 원점(origin) 근처에 유지합니다. 노이즈를 완화하기 위해 asymmetric view alignment mechanism을 도입하여, 신뢰할 수 있는 view가 신뢰도가 낮은 view를 단방향으로 안내하도록 합니다. 또한 consensus-aware cluster learning 전략을 설계하여 confidence-based screening scheme을 통해 견고한 global pseudo-label을 구성하고, cluster 구조를 정교화합니다. 13개의 baseline과의 광범위한 실험에서 HAMC가 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성함을 보였습니다.</p>"},{"id":"61330","en":"WET: Mitigating World-Conditioned Knowledge Conflicts via World Entropy Tethering","ko":"WET: World Entropy Tethering을 통한 World-Conditioned 지식 충돌 완화","authors":"Zixuan Wang, Yifei He, Zihan Wang, Kun Wang, Chaomeng chen","pos":"#4013","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=rGTNcRMOxF","abs":"<p>Large language models (LLMs) face a \"loyalty dilemma\" when correctness is conditioned on an active world-of-discourse. We identify a systemic failure mode---world misattribution---where models implicitly ground generation in an incompatible regime and drift from the target world. We propose World Entropy Tethering (WET), an inference-time monitor-and-tether: a world-entropy probe flags drift risk on prompt anchors, and a conditional score matching geometry model identifies tethering heads for entropy-gated rescaling. Experiments show: (I) Linear Separability: world labels are linearly decodable from internal states; (II) Geometric Drift: hallucinations are preceded by measurable deviations from the target world region; and (III) Targeted Mitigation: WET improves world consistency and reduces hallucination rates by up to 22.4% without compromising generation quality. Code is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/WET-ADA0/.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large language models (LLMs)는 정확성이 활성화된 world-of-discourse에 조건부로 의존할 때 \"loyalty dilemma\"에 직면한다. 우리는 모델이 암묵적으로 생성 결과를 호환되지 않는 regime에 grounding하고 target world에서 이탈하는 체계적 실패 모드인 --- world misattribution ---을 식별한다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 inference-time monitor-and-tether인 World Entropy Tethering (WET)를 제안한다. world-entropy probe가 prompt anchor에서 drift risk를 감지하고, conditional score matching geometry model이 entropy-gated rescaling을 위한 tethering head를 식별한다. 실험 결과는 다음을 보여준다: (I) Linear Separability: world label은 내부 상태로부터 선형적으로 복호화될 수 있다; (II) Geometric Drift: hallucination은 target world region으로부터 측정 가능한 편차에 선행된다; (III) Targeted Mitigation: WET는 생성 품질을 저하시키지 않으면서 world consistency를 향상시키고 hallucination rate를 최대 22.4%까지 감소시킨다. 코드는 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/WET-ADA0/ 에서 제공된다.</p>"},{"id":"67070","en":"Position: Interestingness is an Inductive Heuristic for Future Compression Progress","ko":"Position: 흥미로움은 미래 압축 진전을 위한 귀납적 휴리스틱이다","authors":"Vincent Herrmann, Jürgen Schmidhuber","pos":"#4107","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=pSk9fbvagp","abs":"<p>This position paper argues that truly open-ended intelligence is bottlenecked by the challenge of <em>interestingness</em>: the ability to prospectively identify which tasks or data hold the potential for future progress. We formalize interestingness as an inductive heuristic for future compression progress and investigate its predictability using tools from Kolmogorov Complexity and Algorithmic Statistics. By analyzing complexity-runtime profiles under various priors over computable objects, we demonstrate that the <em>inductive property of interestingness</em>—the capacity for past compression progress to signal future discovery—is theoretically viable. However, we show that this property is highly sensitive to the underlying distribution of objects. We conclude by calling for a move beyond human-in-the-loop filtering or data creation, and a shift toward <em>introspective</em> models that can explicitly assess their own potential for insight. Furthermore, we advocate the engineering of scale-free synthetic environments, providing a principled roadmap for the development of truly autonomous open-ended systems.</p>"},{"id":"60885","en":"Evaluating AI Grading on Real-World Handwritten College Mathematics: A Large-Scale Study Toward a Benchmark","ko":"실제 손글씨 대학 수학 답안에서 AI 채점 평가: Benchmark를 향한 대규모 연구","authors":"Zhiqi Yu, Xingping Liu, Haobin Mao, Mingshuo Liu, Long Chen, Jack Xin, Yifeng Yu","pos":"#4311","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=vcdsMrNGqP","abs":"<p>Grading in large undergraduate STEM courses often yields minimal feedback due to heavy instructional workloads. We present a large-scale empirical study of AI grading on real, handwritten single-variable calculus work from a major U.S. public research university. Using OCR-conditioned large language models with structured, rubric-guided prompting, our system produces scores and formative feedback for thousands of free-response quiz submissions from nearly 800 students. In a setting with no single ground-truth label, we evaluate performance against official teaching-assistant grades, student surveys, and independent human review, finding strong alignment with TA scoring and a large majority of AI-generated feedback rated as correct or acceptable across quizzes.  Beyond calculus, this setting highlights core challenges in OCR-conditioned mathematical reasoning and partial-credit assessment. We analyze key failure modes, propose practical rubric- and prompt-design principles, and introduce a multi-perspective evaluation protocol for reliable, real-course deployment. Building on the dataset and evaluation framework developed here, we outline a standardized benchmark for AI grading of handwritten mathematics to support reproducible comparison and future research.</p>","absKo":"<p>대규모 undergraduate STEM course에서의 grading은 과도한 강의 부담 때문에 종종 최소한의 feedback만을 제공한다. 우리는 미국의 한 주요 공립 연구대학에서 실제 손글씨 단일 변수 calculus 과제를 대상으로 AI grading에 대한 대규모 실증 연구를 제시한다. structured하고 rubric-guided prompting을 사용하는 OCR-conditioned large language model을 통해, 우리 시스템은 거의 800명의 학생으로부터 제출된 수천 개의 free-response quiz에 대해 score와 formative feedback을 생성한다. 단일 ground-truth label이 없는 설정에서, 우리는 공식 teaching-assistant grade, student survey, 독립적인 human review와 비교하여 성능을 평가하며, quiz 전반에 걸쳐 TA scoring과의 높은 일치도와 AI가 생성한 feedback의 대다수가 correct 또는 acceptable로 평가됨을 확인한다. calculus를 넘어, 이 설정은 OCR-conditioned mathematical reasoning과 partial-credit assessment의 핵심 과제를 드러낸다. 우리는 주요 failure mode를 분석하고, 실용적인 rubric 및 prompt design 원칙을 제안하며, 신뢰할 수 있는 실제 강의 배포를 위한 multi-perspective evaluation protocol을 도입한다. 여기서 개발한 dataset과 evaluation framework를 바탕으로, 재현 가능한 비교와 향후 연구를 지원하기 위한 손글씨 수학 AI grading의 표준화된 benchmark를 제시한다.</p>"},{"id":"66316","en":"Beyond Text-to-SQL: Can LLMs Really Debug Enterprise ETL SQL?","ko":"Text-to-SQL을 넘어서: LLM은 실제로 기업 ETL SQL을 디버깅할 수 있는가?","authors":"Jing Ye, Yiwen Duan, Yonghong Yu, Victor Ma, Yang Gao, Xing Chen","pos":"#504","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=4ltyJqAHMg","abs":"SQL is central to enterprise data engineering, yet generating fully correct SQL code in a single attempt remains difficult—even for experienced developers and advanced \\ttsql LLMs—often requiring multiple debugging iterations. We introduce \\textbf{\\ourbench}, the first benchmark for enterprise-level SQL reasoning and debugging. Our benchmark is built upon two key innovations: (1) an \\textbf{automated construction workflow} that employs reverse engineering to systematically inject realistic bugs into large-scale SQL code, enabling scalable and diverse benchmark generation; and (2) an \\textbf{execution-free evaluation framework} tailored for enterprise settings, providing fast, accurate, and resource-efficient assessment. \\ourbench comprises $469$ \\ourbenchsyn queries featuring syntax errors with explicit error messages, and $516$ \\ourbenchsem queries targeting semantic errors where codes fails to meet user intent. The queries are highly complex, averaging over $140$ lines, and featuring deep and wide abstract syntax trees (average width $&gt;11$, depth $&gt;8.7$). Evaluation of nearly $30$ LLMs reveals a substantial performance gap: the best-performing model, Claude-4-Sonnet, achieves only $36.46\\%$ accuracy on \\ourbenchsyn and $32.17\\%$ on \\ourbenchsem, while most models score below $20\\%$. We further explore four solution strategies, identify key challenges, and outline promising directions for enterprise SQL debugging with LLMs."},{"id":"63740","en":"XDomainBench: Diagnosing Reasoning Collapse in High-Dimensional Scientific Knowledge Composition","ko":"XDomainBench: 고차원 과학 지식 구성에서의 Reasoning 붕괴 진단","authors":"Zhiren Gong, Tiantong Wu, Jiaming Zhang, Fuyao Zhang, CHE WANG, Yurong Hao, Yikun Hou, Foo Ping, Yilei Zhao, Fei Huang, Chau Yuen, Wei Yang Bryan Lim","pos":"#702","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=U8x5SYtT5b","abs":"<p>Large Language Models (LLMs) are increasingly deployed for knowledge synthesis, yet their capacity for compositional generalization in scientific knowledge remains under-characterized. Existing benchmarks primarily focus on single-turn restricted scenarios, failing to capture the capability boundaries exposed by real-world interactive scientific workflows. To address this, we introduce XDomainBench, a diagnostic benchmark for interactive interdisciplinary scientific reasoning. We formalize the composition order and mixture structure to enable systematic stress-testing from single-discipline to inter-disciplinary, comprising 8,598 interactive sessions across 20 domains and 4 task categories, with 8 realistic trajectory patterns covering difficulty and domain-mixture dynamics, simulating real AI4S scenarios. Large-scale evaluation of LLMs reveals a systematic reasoning collapse as composition order increases, stemming from two root causes: (i) direct difficulty increases induced by domain composition, and (ii) indirect interaction-amplified failures where trajectory patterns trigger error accumulation, reasoning breaks, and domain confusion, ultimately leading to session collapse.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large Language Models(LLM)은 knowledge synthesis에 점점 더 많이 활용되고 있지만, scientific knowledge에서의 compositional generalization 능력은 아직 충분히 규명되지 않았다. 기존 benchmark는 주로 단일 턴의 제한된 시나리오에 초점을 맞추어, 실제 세계의 상호작용적 scientific workflow에서 드러나는 capability boundary를 포착하지 못한다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 상호작용적 interdisciplinary scientific reasoning을 위한 진단 benchmark인 XDomainBench를 제안한다. 우리는 composition order와 mixture structure를 정식화하여 single-discipline에서 inter-disciplinary까지 체계적인 stress-testing이 가능하도록 했으며, 20개 domain과 4개 task category에 걸친 8,598개의 interactive session으로 구성된다. 또한 난이도와 domain-mixture dynamics를 아우르는 8개의 realistic trajectory pattern을 포함하여 실제 AI4S 시나리오를 모사한다. 대규모 LLM 평가 결과, composition order가 증가할수록 체계적인 reasoning collapse가 발생함을 보였으며, 그 근본 원인은 두 가지다. (i) domain composition이 유발하는 직접적인 난이도 증가, (ii) trajectory pattern이 error accumulation, reasoning break, domain confusion을 촉발하여 결국 session collapse로 이어지는 간접적 상호작용 증폭 실패이다.</p>"},{"id":"65517","en":"Towards Solving the Gilbert-Pollak Conjecture via Large Language Models","ko":"Large Language Model을 통한 Gilbert-Pollak 추측 해결을 향하여","authors":"Yisi Ke, Tianyu Huang, Yankai Shu, Di He, Jingchu Gai, Liwei Wang","pos":"#703","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Cqq3HGRIuM","abs":"The Gilbert-Pollak Conjecture, also known as the Steiner Ratio Conjecture, states that for any finite point set in the Euclidean plane, the Steiner minimum tree has length at least $\\sqrt{3}/2 \\approx 0.866$ times that of the Euclidean minimum spanning tree (the Steiner ratio). A sequence of improvements through the 1980s culminated in a lower bound of $0.824$, with no substantial progress reported over the past three decades. Recent advances in LLMs have demonstrated strong performance on contest-level mathematical problems, yet their potential for addressing open, research-level questions remains largely unexplored. In this work, we present a novel AI system for obtaining tighter lower bounds on the Steiner ratio. Rather than directly prompting LLMs to solve the conjecture, we task them with generating rule-constrained geometric lemmas implemented as executable code. These lemmas are then used to construct a collection of specialized functions, which we call verification functions, that yield theoretically certified lower bounds of the Steiner ratio. Through progressive lemma refinement driven by reflection, the system establishes a new certified lower bound of 0.8559 for the Steiner ratio. The entire research effort involves only thousands of LLM calls,  demonstrating the strong potential of LLM-based systems for advanced mathematical research."},{"id":"60732","en":"Towards Professional-Grade Financial Agents: Benchmarking, Tooling, and Structured Reasoning","ko":"전문가 수준의 금융 Agent를 향하여: 벤치마킹, 도구화, 구조적 추론","authors":"Cheng Huang, Jinghua Piao, Wang Ranran, Yong Li","pos":"#704","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=x6nNQBumUQ","abs":"<p>Financial reasoning requires precise execution. While Large Language Model (LLM) agents have shown encouraging progress in financial reasoning, their effectiveness in realistic financial workflows is severely hindered by the lack of holistic benchmarks and the fragility of unstructured reasoning. To evaluate these capabilities, we introduce ProFinR, the first Professional Finance Reasoning benchmark that covers four types of financial tasks, comprising 528 expert-designed tasks. To solve these complex financial reasoning questions, we construct Financial Tool Universe, a tool library containing 53 domain-specific tools organized into 13 categories. Building on the tool library, we introduce ProFinAgents, a structured agent framework based on Directed Acyclic Graph (DAG) and Case-Based Memory (CBM). Compared with strictly sequential workflows, ProFinAgent coordinates tool execution through DAG. This allows for parallel execution and reduces latency compared to serial pipelines. Furthermore, the CBM component refines decision-making over time by retrieving prior cases to mitigate reasoning failures. Experimental results demonstrate that ProFinAgent achieves a 49.81% performance gain over state-of-the-art baselines with a 47.1% reduction in inference latency.</p>","absKo":"<p>Financial reasoning에는 정밀한 실행이 요구된다. Large Language Model (LLM) agent가 financial reasoning에서 고무적인 진전을 보였지만, 현실적인 금융 workflow에서의 효율성은 포괄적 benchmark의 부재와 비구조화된 추론의 취약성 때문에 심각하게 제약된다. 이러한 역량을 평가하기 위해, 우리는 4가지 유형의 금융 과제를 포괄하고 528개의 전문가 설계 과제로 구성된 최초의 Professional Finance Reasoning benchmark인 ProFinR을 제안한다. 이러한 복잡한 금융 추론 질문을 해결하기 위해, 우리는 13개 범주로 조직된 53개의 도메인 특화 tool을 포함하는 tool library인 Financial Tool Universe를 구축한다. 이 tool library를 바탕으로, 우리는 Directed Acyclic Graph (DAG)와 Case-Based Memory (CBM)에 기반한 구조화된 agent framework인 ProFinAgents를 제안한다. 엄격하게 순차적인 workflow와 비교했을 때, ProFinAgent는 DAG를 통해 tool 실행을 조율한다. 이를 통해 병렬 실행이 가능해지고, serial pipeline에 비해 latency가 감소한다. 더 나아가 CBM 구성요소는 과거 case를 검색하여 추론 실패를 완화함으로써 시간이 지남에 따라 의사결정을 개선한다. 실험 결과, ProFinAgent는 state-of-the-art baseline 대비 49.81%의 성능 향상과 47.1%의 inference latency 감소를 달성함을 보였다.</p>"},{"id":"61449","en":"TestExplora: Benchmarking LLMs for Proactive Bug Discovery via Repository-Level Test Generation","ko":"TestExplora: Repository 수준 테스트 생성으로 LLM의 선제적 버그 발견 벤치마킹","authors":"Steven Liu, Jane Luo, Xin Zhang, Aofan Liu, Hao Liu, Jie Wu, Ziyang Huang, Yangyu Huang, Yu Kang, Scarlett Li","pos":"#705","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=pxw9YfTYtC","abs":"Given that Large Language Models (LLMs) are increasingly applied to automate software development, comprehensive software assurance spans three distinct goals: regression prevention, reactive reproduction, and proactive discovery. Current evaluations systematically overlook the third goal. Specifically, they either constrain models to a compliance trap by treating existing code as the ground truth for regression prevention, or rely on post-failure artifacts (e.g., issue reports) for reactive bug reproduction, failing to expose defects before they manifest as failures. To bridge this gap, we present TestExplora, a benchmark designed to evaluate LLMs as proactive testers within full-scale, realistic repository environments. Comprising 2,389 tasks across 482 repositories, TestExplora conceals all defect-related information, forcing models to uncover bugs by identifying discrepancies between implementation and documentation-derived intent—utilizing documentation as the reference oracle. Furthermore, to ensure sustainable evaluation and mitigate risks of data leakage in static datasets, we propose a continuous, time-aware data collection framework. Our evaluation reveals a significant capability gap: state-of-the-art models achieve a maximum Fail-to-Pass ($F2P$) rate of only 16.06%. Further analysis indicates that navigating complex cross-module interactions and leveraging agentic exploration are critical to advancing LLMs toward autonomous software quality assurance. Consistent with this, SWEAgent instantiated with GPT-5-mini achieves an $F2P$ of 17.27% and an $F2P@5$ of 29.7%, highlighting the effectiveness and promise of agentic exploration in proactive bug discovery tasks.","absKo":"대규모 언어 모델(LLM)이 소프트웨어 개발 자동화에 점점 더 많이 적용됨에 따라, 포괄적인 software assurance는 세 가지 서로 다른 목표를 포괄한다. 즉, regression prevention, reactive reproduction, 그리고 proactive discovery이다. 현재의 평가는 이 세 번째 목표를 체계적으로 간과한다. 구체적으로, 기존 코드를 ground truth로 취급해 regression prevention에만 초점을 맞추어 모델을 compliance trap에 가두거나, 아니면 issue report와 같은 post-failure artifact에 의존하여 reactive bug reproduction을 수행함으로써, failure로 드러나기 전에 결함을 노출하지 못한다. 이러한 격차를 메우기 위해 우리는 대규모의 현실적인 repository 환경에서 proactive tester로서의 LLM을 평가하도록 설계된 benchmark인 TestExplora를 제시한다. 482개 repository에 걸친 2,389개 task로 구성된 TestExplora는 모든 defect 관련 정보를 숨겨 두어, 문서를 reference oracle로 활용하면서 구현과 documentation-derived intent 사이의 불일치를 식별함으로써 버그를 찾아내도록 모델을 강제한다. 더 나아가, 지속 가능한 평가를 보장하고 정적 dataset에서의 data leakage 위험을 완화하기 위해 우리는 continuous time-aware data collection framework를 제안한다. 우리의 평가는 상당한 능력 격차를 드러낸다. state-of-the-art 모델들의 최대 Fail-to-Pass($F2P$) 비율은 16.06%에 불과하다. 추가 분석은 복잡한 cross-module interaction을 탐색하고 agentic exploration을 활용하는 능력이 LLM을 자율적 software quality assurance로 발전시키는 데 핵심적임을 보여준다. 이와 일관되게, GPT-5-mini를 탑재한 SWEAgent는 17.27%의 $F2P$와 29.7%의 $F2P@5$를 달성하여, proactive bug discovery task에서 agentic exploration의 효과와 가능성을 강조한다."},{"id":"66626","en":"SpreadsheetArena: Decomposing Preference in LLM Generation of Spreadsheet Workbooks","ko":"SpreadsheetArena: LLM의 스프레드시트 워크북 생성에서 선호 분해","authors":"Srivatsa Kundurthy, Clara Na, Michael Handley, Zach Kirshner, Chen Bo Calvin Zhang, Manasi Sharma, Emma Strubell, John Ling","pos":"#707","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=20x0qoSG2f","abs":"<p>Large language models (LLMs) are increasingly tasked with producing and manipulating structured artifacts.  We consider the task of end-to-end <strong>spreadsheet generation</strong>, where language models are prompted to produce spreadsheet artifacts to satisfy users' explicit and implicit constraints, specified in natural language.  We introduce <strong>SpreadsheetArena</strong>, a platform for evaluating models' performance on the task via blind pairwise evaluations of LLM-generated spreadsheet workbooks. As with other complex, open-ended tasks, relevant evaluation criteria can vary substantially across use cases and prompts, often in ways that are difficult to formalize. Compared to general chat or text generation settings, spreadsheet generation presents unique challenges and opportunities: the task output structure is well-defined and multi-dimensional, and there are often complex considerations around interactivity and layout. Among other findings, we observe that stylistic, structural, and functional features of preferred spreadsheets vary substantially across use cases, and expert evaluations of spreadsheets for finance prompts suggests that even highly ranked arena models do not reliably produce spreadsheets aligned with domain-specific best practices. Our hope is that our work prompts further study of end-to-end spreadsheet generation as a challenging and interesting category of complex, open-ended tasks for LLMs. Our live arena is hosted at https://spreadsheetarena.ai.</p>"},{"id":"66745","en":"SWE-fficiency: Can Language Models Optimize Real-World Repositories on Real Workloads?","ko":"SWE-fficiency: 언어 모델이 실제 워크로드에서 실제 저장소를 최적화할 수 있는가?","authors":"Jeffrey Ma, Milad Hashemi, Amir Yazdanbakhsh, Kevin Swersky, Ofir Press, Enhui Li, Vijay Janapa Reddi, Parthasarathy Ranganathan","pos":"#708","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=0pyFbZSfbT","abs":"<p>Optimizing the performance of large-scale software repositories demands expertise in code reasoning and software engineering (SWE) to reduce runtime while preserving program correctness. However, most benchmarks emphasize what to fix rather than how to fix code. We introduce SWE-fficiency, a benchmark for evaluating repository-level performance optimization on real workloads. Our suite contains 498 tasks across nine widely used data-science, machine-learning, and HPC repositories (e.g., numpy, pandas, scipy): given a complete codebase and a slow workload, an agent must investigate code semantics, localize bottlenecks and relevant tests, and produce a patch that matches or exceeds expert speedup while passing the same unit tests. To enable this how-to-fix evaluation, our automated pipeline scrapes GitHub pull requests for performance-improving edits, combining keyword filtering, static analysis, coverage tooling, and execution validation to both confirm expert speedup baselines and identify relevant repository unit tests. Empirical evaluation of state-of-the-art agents reveals significant underperformance. On average, top agents achieve less than 0.23x the expert speedup: agents struggle in localizing optimization opportunities, reasoning about execution across functions, and maintaining correctness in proposed edits. We release the benchmark and accompanying data pipeline to facilitate research on automated performance engineering and long-horizon software reasoning.</p>"},{"id":"60614","en":"QuArch: A Benchmark for Evaluating LLM Reasoning in Computer Architecture","ko":"QuArch: 컴퓨터 아키텍처에서 LLM 추론 평가를 위한 벤치마크","authors":"Shvetank Prakash, Andrew Cheng, Arya Tschand, Mark Mazumder, Varun Gohil, Jeffrey Ma, Jason Yik, Zishen Wan, Jessica A. Quaye, Elisavet Alvanaki, Avinash Kumar, Chandrashis Mazumdar, Tuhin Khare, Alexander Ingare, Ikechukwu Uchendu, Radhika Ghosal, Abhishek Tyagi, Chenyu Wang, Andrea Mattia Garavagno, Sarah Gu, Alice Guo, Grace Hur, Luca Carloni, Tushar Krishna, Ankita Nayak, Amir Yazdanbakhsh, Vijay Janapa Reddi","pos":"#709","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=yU6X1XZl8t","abs":"<p>The field of computer architecture, which bridges high-level software abstractions and low-level hardware implementations, remains absent from current large language model (LLM) evaluations. To this end, we present QuArch (pronounced 'quark'), the first benchmark designed to facilitate the development and evaluation of LLM knowledge and reasoning capabilities specifically in computer architecture. QuArch provides a comprehensive collection of 2,671 expert-validated question-answer (QA) pairs covering various aspects of computer architecture, including processor design, memory systems, and interconnection networks. Our evaluation reveals that while frontier models possess domain-specific knowledge, they struggle with skills that require higher-order thinking in computer architecture. Frontier model accuracies vary widely (from 34% to 73%) on these advanced questions, highlighting persistent gaps in architectural reasoning across analysis, design, and implementation QAs. Furthermore, via fine-tuning we find that QuArch can translate to improved performance on a realistic memory hierarchy design task, resulting in up to 1.99x more area-efficient solutions and up to 40% more viable solutions overall. By holistically assessing fundamental skills, QuArch provides a foundation for building and measuring LLM capabilities that can accelerate innovation in computing systems.</p>","absKo":"<p>컴퓨터 아키텍처 분야는 고수준 소프트웨어 추상화와 저수준 하드웨어 구현을 연결하는 분야이지만, 현재의 large language model (LLM) 평가에서는 여전히 빠져 있다. 이를 위해 우리는 컴퓨터 아키텍처에서의 LLM 지식 및 추론 능력의 개발과 평가를 촉진하기 위해 설계된 최초의 benchmark인 QuArch(‘quark’로 발음)를 제안한다. QuArch는 processor design, memory systems, interconnection networks를 포함해 컴퓨터 아키텍처의 다양한 측면을 포괄하는 2,671개의 expert-validated question-answer (QA) pair로 구성된 종합적 모음이다. 우리의 평가 결과, frontier model들은 도메인별 지식은 갖추고 있지만 컴퓨터 아키텍처에서 higher-order thinking이 필요한 기술에서는 여전히 어려움을 겪는다. frontier model의 정확도는 이러한 고난도 질문에서 34%에서 73%까지 크게 달라지며, analysis, design, implementation QA 전반에 걸친 architectural reasoning의 지속적인 격차를 드러낸다. 더 나아가 fine-tuning을 통해 QuArch가 현실적인 memory hierarchy design task의 성능 향상으로 이어질 수 있음을 확인했으며, 그 결과 area 효율이 최대 1.99배 더 높은 해와 전체적으로 최대 40% 더 많은 viable solution을 얻었다. 기본 기술을 총체적으로 평가하는 QuArch는 컴퓨팅 시스템 혁신을 가속할 수 있는 LLM 능력을 구축하고 측정하기 위한 기반을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"64384","en":"MALICE: Memory-aware Loop Invariants Generation on Symbolic Execution Traces","ko":"MALICE: 기호 실행 궤적에서 메모리 인식 루프 불변량 생성","authors":"Tong Chen, Siyu Liu, Hongyi Zhong, liao zhang, Lixiang Wang, Xiwei Wu, Junchi Yan, Qinxiang Cao","pos":"#712","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=O7Vf0wNY2T","abs":"<p>Automatic loop invariant generation remains a challenging problem in program verification, particularly for memory-manipulating programs where shape invariants are required to characterize heap-allocated structures and memory layouts. While existing approaches succeed on numerical invariants, they achieve limited accuracy on shape invariants. We hypothesize that this stems from the need to reason about memory state evolution—information that remains implicit in source code. To address this, we ground LLM reasoning in symbolic execution traces that explicitly capture such transitions.  We propose \\textsc{Malice}, a two-stage framework incorporating these traces: (1) guided multi-step reasoning that predicts invariants via chain-of-thought analysis of traces, and (2) agentic iterative refinement that corrects candidates through verification tool feedback. Evaluated on LIG-MM+, a benchmark featuring common operations on typical memory structures, \\textsc{Malice} substantially outperforms existing approaches.</p>","absKo":"<p>자동 루프 불변식 생성은 프로그램 검증에서 여전히 어려운 문제이며, 특히 shape invariant가 heap-allocated 구조와 memory layout을 특징짓는 데 필요한 memory-manipulating program에서는 더욱 그렇다. 기존 방법들은 수치 불변식에서는 성과를 보이지만, shape invariant에서는 정확도가 제한적이다. 우리는 그 원인이 memory state evolution을 추론해야 하기 때문이라고 가정하며, 이러한 전이는 source code에 암묵적으로만 남아 있다고 본다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 이러한 전이를 명시적으로 포착하는 symbolic execution trace에 LLM 추론을 grounding한다. 우리는 이러한 trace를 통합한 2단계 프레임워크 \\textsc{Malice}를 제안한다. (1) chain-of-thought 분석을 통해 trace의 invariants를 예측하는 guided multi-step reasoning, 그리고 (2) verification tool feedback을 통해 후보를 교정하는 agentic iterative refinement이다. 일반적인 memory structure에 대한 전형적 연산을 포함하는 benchmark인 LIG-MM+에서 평가한 결과, \\textsc{Malice}는 기존 방법들을 크게 상회한다.</p>"},{"id":"61417","en":"JAEGER: Joint 3D Audio-Visual Grounding and Reasoning in Simulated Physical Environments","ko":"JAEGER: Simulated Physical Environments에서 Joint 3D Audio-Visual Grounding and Reasoning","authors":"Zhan Liu, Changli Tang, Yuxin WANG, Zhiyuan Zhu, Youjun Chen, Yiwen Shao, TIANZI WANG, Lei Ke, Zengrui Jin, Chao Zhang","pos":"#713","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=qOd7ft1FSQ","abs":"<p>Current audio-visual large language models (AV-LLMs) are predominantly restricted to 2D perception, relying on RGB video and monaural audio. This design choice introduces a fundamental dimensionality mismatch that precludes reliable source localization and spatial reasoning in complex 3D environments. We address this limitation by presenting JAEGER, a framework that extends AV-LLMs to 3D space, to enable joint spatial grounding and reasoning through the integration of RGB-D observations and multi-channel first-order ambisonics. A core contribution of our work is the neural intensity vector (Neural IV), a learned spatial audio representation that encodes robust directional cues to enhance direction-of-arrival estimation, even in adverse acoustic scenarios with overlapping sources. To facilitate large-scale training and systematic evaluation, we propose SpatialSceneQA, a benchmark of 61k instruction-tuning samples curated from simulated physical environments. Extensive experiments demonstrate that our approach consistently surpasses 2D-centric baselines across diverse spatial perception and reasoning tasks, underscoring the necessity of explicit 3D modelling for advancing AI in physical environments. Our source code, pre-trained model checkpoints and datasets will be released upon acceptance.</p>","absKo":"<p>현재의 audio-visual large language model(AV-LLM)은 주로 RGB video와 monaural audio에 의존하는 2D perception에 제한되어 있다. 이러한 설계 선택은 복잡한 3D 환경에서 신뢰할 수 있는 source localization과 spatial reasoning을 가로막는 근본적인 dimensionality mismatch를 초래한다. 우리는 RGB-D observation과 multi-channel first-order ambisonics의 통합을 통해 joint spatial grounding과 reasoning을 가능하게 하도록, AV-LLM을 3D space로 확장하는 framework인 JAEGER를 제시함으로써 이 한계를 해결한다. 우리의 핵심 기여는 방향 도달 추정(direction-of-arrival estimation)을 향상시키기 위해 강건한 방향 단서를 인코딩하는 학습된 spatial audio representation인 neural intensity vector(Neural IV)이다. 특히 겹치는 source가 있는 불리한 acoustic scenario에서도 이를 개선한다. 대규모 학습과 체계적 평가를 용이하게 하기 위해, 우리는 시뮬레이션 물리 환경에서 정제한 61k instruction-tuning sample로 구성된 benchmark인 SpatialSceneQA를 제안한다. 광범위한 실험은 우리의 접근법이 다양한 spatial perception 및 reasoning task에서 2D 중심 baseline을 일관되게 능가하며, 물리적 환경에서 AI를 발전시키기 위해서는 명시적인 3D modelling이 필요함을 강조한다. 소스 코드, pre-trained model checkpoint, dataset은 승인 후 공개될 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"62934","en":"From Guessing to Placeholding:  A Cost-Theoretic Framework for Uncertainty-Aware Code Completion","ko":"추측에서 Placeholding으로: 불확실성 인식 코드 완성을 위한 비용 이론적 프레임워크","authors":"Liang Zhu, Haolin Chen, Lidong Zhao, Xian Wu","pos":"#714","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=bkCPa5RDbm","abs":"<p>While Large Language Models (LLMs) have demonstrated exceptional proficiency in code completion, they typically adhere to a <strong>Hard Completion (HC)</strong> paradigm, compelling the generation of fully concrete code even amidst insufficient context. Our analysis of 3 million real-world interactions exposes the limitations of this strategy: 61% of the generated suggestions were either edited after acceptance or rejected despite exhibiting over 80% similarity to the user's subsequent code, suggesting that models frequently make erroneous predictions at specific token positions. Motivated by this observation, we propose <strong>Adaptive Placeholder Completion (APC)</strong>, a collaborative framework that extends HC by strategically outputting explicit placeholders at high-entropy positions, allowing users to fill directly via IDE navigation. Theoretically, we formulate code completion as a cost-minimization problem under uncertainty. Premised on the observation that filling placeholders incurs lower cost than correcting errors, we prove the existence of a critical entropy threshold above which APC achieves strictly lower expected cost than HC. We instantiate this framework by constructing training data from filtered real-world edit logs and design a cost-based reward function for reinforcement learning. Extensive evaluations across 1.5B--14B parameter models demonstrate that APC reduces expected editing costs from 19% to 50% while preserving standard HC performance. Our work provides both a theoretical foundation and a practical training framework for uncertainty-aware code completion, demonstrating that adaptive abstention can be learned end-to-end without sacrificing conventional completion quality.</p>","absKo":"<p>대규모 언어 모델(LLM)은 code completion에서 탁월한 성능을 보여 왔지만, 일반적으로 <strong>Hard Completion (HC)</strong> 패러다임을 따르며, 맥락이 충분하지 않은 상황에서도 완전히 구체적인 코드를 생성하도록 강제된다. 실제 300만 건의 상호작용을 분석한 결과, 이 전략의 한계가 드러났다. 생성된 제안의 61%는 수락된 뒤 수정되었거나, 사용자의 이후 코드와 80% 이상 유사했음에도 거부되었으며, 이는 모델이 특정 token 위치에서 빈번하게 잘못된 예측을 한다는 것을 시사한다. 이러한 관찰에 동기를 얻어, 우리는 <strong>Adaptive Placeholder Completion (APC)</strong>를 제안한다. APC는 HC를 확장한 협력적 프레임워크로, 높은 entropy 위치에서 명시적 placeholder를 전략적으로 출력하여 사용자가 IDE navigation을 통해 직접 채울 수 있게 한다. 이론적으로 우리는 code completion을 불확실성 하에서의 비용 최소화 문제로 정식화한다. placeholder를 채우는 비용이 오류를 수정하는 비용보다 낮다는 관찰에 근거하여, 우리는 APC가 HC보다 기대 비용이 엄격하게 더 낮아지는 임계 entropy threshold의 존재를 증명한다. 우리는 필터링된 실제 편집 로그로부터 training data를 구성하고, reinforcement learning을 위한 cost-based reward function을 설계함으로써 이 프레임워크를 구현한다. 1.5B--14B parameter model에 걸친 광범위한 평가에서 APC는 표준 HC 성능을 유지하면서 기대 편집 비용을 19%에서 50%까지 줄이는 것으로 나타났다. 우리의 연구는 uncertainty-aware code completion에 대한 이론적 기반과 실용적 training framework를 모두 제공하며, adaptive abstention이 전통적인 completion 품질을 희생하지 않고 end-to-end로 학습될 수 있음을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"63166","en":"EvoC2F: Compiling Tool Orchestration for Efficient and Evolvable LLM Agents","ko":"EvoC2F: 효율적이고 진화 가능한 LLM 에이전트를 위한 도구 오케스트레이션 컴파일","authors":"Lei Wei, Qi Liu, Ruiyang Huang, Xiao Peng, TT, Lanbo Lin, Chenhao Jiang, Yuanwu Xu, Tianyuan Yang, Jiayao Liu, Li Cai, Yuying Li, Bin Wang","pos":"#716","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ZSGB91kMOG","abs":"<p>Tool-augmented language model agents have shown great potential in solving complex real-world tasks, but a key challenge remains balancing planning flexibility with the reliability required for production deployment. Existing approaches either execute tools sequentially without parallelism or generate unconstrained code, hindering optimization and verification. Additionally, agents that learn from experience often suffer from skill library pollution, where unverified abstractions degrade performance over time. We propose EvoC2F, a framework that redefines tool orchestration through program compilation and verified continuous learning. By constraining plan generation to a well-defined intermediate representation with explicit semantic annotations, EvoC2F enables provably correct optimizations, parallelism, and fault tolerance, while ensuring soundness guarantees. Our verification-gated code-to-function evolution process ensures that learned skills undergo rigorous testing before library admission. Experiments across diverse benchmarks demonstrate that EvoC2F outperforms existing methods, reducing latency and establishing a robust foundation for building reliable, evolving autonomous agents. Our code and datasets are available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/EvoC2F-1DEF/.</p>","absKo":"<p>Tool이 강화된 language model agent는 복잡한 실제 task를 해결하는 데 큰 잠재력을 보여주었지만, 핵심 과제는 planning flexibility와 production deployment에 필요한 신뢰성 사이의 균형이다. 기존 접근법은 tool을 병렬성 없이 순차적으로 실행하거나 제약 없는 코드를 생성하여 최적화와 검증을 어렵게 만든다. 또한 경험으로부터 학습하는 agent는 종종 skill library pollution을 겪는데, 검증되지 않은 abstraction이 시간이 지남에 따라 성능을 저하시킨다. 우리는 프로그램 컴파일과 검증된 지속 학습을 통해 tool orchestration을 재정의하는 framework인 EvoC2F를 제안한다. 명시적 semantic annotation이 있는 잘 정의된 intermediate representation으로 plan 생성을 제한함으로써, EvoC2F는 증명 가능한 올바른 최적화, 병렬성, fault tolerance를 가능하게 하고 soundness 보장을 제공한다. verification-gated code-to-function 진화 과정은 학습된 skill이 library에 편입되기 전에 엄격한 테스트를 거치도록 보장한다. 다양한 benchmark에서의 실험은 EvoC2F가 기존 방법을 능가하고, 지연 시간을 줄이며, 신뢰할 수 있고 진화하는 autonomous agent를 구축하기 위한 견고한 기반을 확립함을 보여준다. 코드와 데이터셋은 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/EvoC2F-1DEF/ 에서 제공된다.</p>"},{"id":"66321","en":"SpaceVista: All-Scale Visual Spatial Reasoning from mm to km","ko":"SpaceVista: mm에서 km까지 전 스케일 시각 공간 추론","authors":"Peiwen Sun, Shiqiang Lang, Dongming Wu, Ding Yi, Kaituo Feng, Huadai Liu, Zhen Ye, Rui Liu, Yun-Hui Liu, Jianan Wang, Xiangyu Yue","pos":"#805","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=4i4K7wVYUW","abs":"<p>With the current surge in spatial reasoning, researchers have made significant progress in understanding indoor scenes, but still struggle with more diverse applications. This paper aims to advance all-scale spatial reasoning by tackling two key challenges: 1) the heavy reliance on indoor 3D scans and labor-intensive annotations for dataset curation; 2) the absence of all-scale modeling, which often leads to overfitting to single scenes. In this paper, we introduce a holistic solution that integrates a structured spatial reasoning knowledge system, scale-aware modeling, and a progressive training paradigm, as the <strong>first attempt</strong> to broaden the scope of all-scale spatial intelligence. Using a task-specific, specialist-driven automated pipeline, we curate over 38K video scenes across 5 spatial scales to create <strong>SpaceVista-1M</strong>, a dataset comprising 1M spatial QAs spanning 19 diverse tasks. While specialist models offer valuable domain knowledge, they are often unreliable evaluators.  Therefore, we build an all-scale benchmark with precise annotations by manually recording and retrieving videos. Nevertheless, naive training with SpaceVista-1M often yields suboptimal results due to the potential knowledge conflict. Accordingly, we introduce <strong>SpaceVista-7B</strong>, a spatial reasoning model that accepts inputs beyond semantics and uses scale as an anchor for scale-aware experts and progressive rewards. Finally, extensive evaluations across 5 benchmarks, including our <strong>SpaceVista-Bench</strong>, demonstrate competitive performance, showcasing generalization across all scales and scenarios. All materials will be released at https://mm2km.github.io/.</p>"},{"id":"65386","en":"From Intent to Solver Code: Semantic Alignment in Optimization Modeling","ko":"의도에서 솔버 코드로: 최적화 모델링에서의 의미 정합","authors":"Yansen Zhang, Qingcan Kang, Yujie chen, Yufei Wang, Xiongwei Han, Tao Zhong, Mingxuan Yuan, Chen Ma","pos":"#2413","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=E9SXR70XyN","abs":"<p>Large language models (LLMs) have opened new paradigms in optimization modeling by enabling the generation of executable solver code from natural language descriptions. Despite this promise, existing approaches typically remain solver-driven: they rely on single-pass forward generation and apply limited post-hoc fixes based on solver error messages, leaving undetected semantic errors that silently produce syntactically correct but logically flawed models. To address this challenge, we propose SAC-Opt, a backward-guided correction framework that grounds optimization modeling in problem semantics rather than solver feedback. At each step, SAC-Opt aligns the original semantic anchors with those reconstructed from the generated code and selectively corrects only the mismatched components, driving convergence toward a semantically faithful model. This anchor-driven correction enables fine-grained refinement of constraint and objective logic, enhancing both fidelity and robustness without requiring additional training or supervision. Empirical results on seven public datasets demonstrate that SAC-Opt improves average modeling accuracy by 7.7%, with gains of up to 21.9% on the ComplexLP dataset. These findings highlight the importance of semantic-anchored correction in LLM-based optimization workflows to ensure faithful translation from problem intent to solver-executable code.</p>"},{"id":"66137","en":"Fix the Mind, Not the Move: Interpretable AI Assistance via Knowledge-Gap Localization","ko":"행동이 아닌 사고를 고쳐라: 지식 격차 국소화를 통한 해석 가능한 AI 보조","authors":"Ayano Hiranaka, Ya-Chuan Hsu, Stefanos Nikolaidis, Erdem Biyik, Daniel Seita","pos":"#715","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=6Yz4cXKkOy","abs":"<p>AI assistants in human-AI collaboration often correct suboptimal human actions through behavioral feedback (e.g., alerts or steering-wheel nudges in assistive driving). Such interventions can mitigate immediate errors, but long-term improvement requires addressing the underlying misconceptions that cause repeated mistakes. We introduce SENSEI, a framework that infers user misconceptions from interaction behavior and provides targeted, minimal yet sufficient suggestions to correct them. Our approach departs from action- or trajectory-level interventions by operating over a structured knowledge representation to localize and correct the sources of erroneous behavior. Across three long-horizon tasks with diverse misconceptions and corresponding behaviors, SENSEI demonstrates zero-shot compositional generalization, disentangling multiple overlapping misconceptions despite training only on single-misconception cases.  A user study further shows that our method identifies real human misconceptions and provides effective guidance that improves long-horizon task performance, successfully correcting 90% of student misconceptions.</p>"},{"id":"63279","en":"LithoDreamer: A Physics-Informed World Model for Multi-Stage Computational Lithography","ko":"LithoDreamer: 다단계 계산 리소그래피를 위한 물리 기반 월드 모델","authors":"Yuqi Jiang, Yumeng Liu, Zimu Li, Jinyuan Deng, Qian Jin, Yucheng Cui, YU LI, Xunzhao Yin, Qi Sun, Cheng Zhuo","pos":"#3601","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=YQmrP0zjmh","abs":"<p>As semiconductor technology nodes continue to shrink, computational lithography has become critical to yield and performance. However, real-world lithography is a continuous, multi-stage physical process driven by implicit interventions, which cannot be captured by the existing static or stage-wise models. To address these issues, we present \\textbf{LithoDreamer}, the first physics-informed World Model (WM) framework for computational lithography, designed to represent the ``Layout-Mask-Resist Image-After Development Image (ADI)'' pipeline as a decision-driven multi-stage physical evolution system, enabling multi-step latent state rollouts within stages and intervention-aware decision-making across stages. First, we learn the feature variations between adjacent states in latent spaces to capture the physical dynamics of each stage. Second, the model plans continuous process interventions through physical mappings in the spaces, which in turn drive subsequent state transitions. Furthermore, we propose a contrastive variational optimization paradigm that jointly explores the evolutions of the interventions and states without discrete action supervision, enabling stable and continuous process rollouts in the WM. Extensive experiments show that LithoDreamer achieves state-of-the-art accuracy and generalization performance.</p>","absKo":"<p>반도체 technology node가 계속 축소됨에 따라 computational lithography는 수율과 성능에 매우 중요해졌다. 그러나 실제 lithography는 암묵적 intervention에 의해 구동되는 연속적이고 다단계인 물리 과정이며, 기존의 정적 모델이나 stage-wise 모델로는 이를 포착할 수 없다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 computational lithography를 위한 최초의 physics-informed World Model (WM) framework인 \\textbf{LithoDreamer}를 제안한다. 이 framework는 ``Layout-Mask-Resist Image-After Development Image (ADI)'' pipeline을 decision-driven multi-stage physical evolution system으로 표현하도록 설계되었으며, stage 내부에서는 multi-step latent state rollout을, stage 간에는 intervention-aware decision-making을 가능하게 한다. 첫째, 우리는 latent space에서 인접한 state 간 feature variation을 학습하여 각 stage의 물리적 dynamics를 포착한다. 둘째, 모델은 space 내의 physical mapping을 통해 연속적인 process intervention을 계획하고, 이는 이후의 state transition을 구동한다. 더 나아가, 우리는 discrete action supervision 없이 intervention과 state의 진화를 공동으로 탐색하는 contrastive variational optimization paradigm을 제안하여, WM에서 안정적이고 연속적인 process rollout을 가능하게 한다. 광범위한 실험 결과 LithoDreamer가 최첨단 정확도와 generalization 성능을 달성함을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"62876","en":"EMFormer: Efficient Multi-Scale Transformer for Accumulative Context Weather Forecasting","ko":"EMFormer: 누적 맥락 날씨 예측을 위한 효율적 다중 스케일 Transformer","authors":"hao chen, Tao Han, Jie ZHANG, Song Guo, Fenghua Ling, LEI BAI","pos":"#1203","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=cKztWFFGNE","abs":"Long-term weather forecasting is critical for socioeconomic planning and disaster preparedness. While recent approaches employ finetuning to extend prediction horizons, they remain constrained by the issues of catastrophic forgetting, error accumulation, and high training overhead. To address these limitations, we present a novel pipeline across pretraining, finetuning and forecasting to enhance long‑context modeling while reducing computational overhead. First, we introduce an Efficient Multi‑scale Transformer (EMFormer) to extract multi‑scale features through a single convolution in both training and inference. Based on the new architecture, we further employ an accumulative context finetuning to improve temporal consistency without degrading short‑term accuracy. Additionally, we propose a composite loss that dynamically balances different terms via a sinusoidal weighting, thereby adaptively guiding the optimization trajectory throughout pretraining and finetuning. Experiments show that our approach achieves great performance in weather forecasting and extreme event prediction, substantially improving long-term forecast accuracy. Moreover, EMFormer demonstrates strong generalization on vision benchmarks (ImageNet-1K and ADE20K) while delivering a 5.69$\\times$ speedup over conventional multi-scale modules.","absKo":"장기 날씨 예측은 사회경제적 계획과 재난 대비에 중요하다. 최근의 접근법은 prediction horizon을 늘리기 위해 finetuning을 활용하지만, catastrophic forgetting, error accumulation, 그리고 높은 training overhead의 문제에 여전히 제약된다. 이러한 한계를 해결하기 위해 우리는 long-context modeling을 강화하면서 계산 오버헤드를 줄이기 위한 pretraining, finetuning, forecasting 전반의 새로운 pipeline을 제시한다. 먼저, 우리는 training과 inference 모두에서 단일 convolution으로 multi-scale feature를 추출하는 Efficient Multi-scale Transformer(EMFormer)를 도입한다. 새로운 architecture를 기반으로, 우리는 short-term accuracy를 저하시키지 않으면서 temporal consistency를 높이기 위해 accumulative context finetuning을 추가로 사용한다. 또한, 우리는 sinusoidal weighting을 통해 서로 다른 term의 균형을 동적으로 조절하는 composite loss를 제안하여, pretraining과 finetuning 전반에서 optimization trajectory를 적응적으로 안내한다. 실험 결과, 우리의 접근은 날씨 예측과 극한 이벤트 예측에서 뛰어난 성능을 달성하며, 장기 예보 정확도를 크게 향상시킨다. 더불어 EMFormer는 vision benchmark(ImageNet-1K 및 ADE20K)에서도 강한 일반화 성능을 보이면서, 기존 multi-scale module 대비 5.69$\\times$의 속도 향상을 제공한다."},{"id":"65980","en":"WF-Bench: A Benchmark for Neural-Network WaveFunction Expressivity and Scaling Laws","ko":"WF-Bench: 신경망 파동함수 표현력 및 스케일링 법칙 벤치마크","authors":"Lixing Zhang, Guijing Duan, Di Luo","pos":"#1112","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=8Fhq7QpYfI","abs":"<p>We present a comprehensive benchmarking dataset and empirical scaling-law analysis for neural network wavefunctions by matching them to a wide spectrum of famous many-body target wavefunctions. The dataset, WF-Bench, spans multiple distinct regimes of strongly correlated quantum matter, including topological states, Wigner crystals, and superconducting wavefunctions, providing a diverse and challenging test bed for neural-network wavefunction expressivity. We introduce a systematic and reproducible benchmarking protocol for target wavefunction matching, enabling consistent performance evaluation across different neural network wavefunction architectures. By using wavefunction fidelity as the uniform metric, we discover empirical scaling laws that characterize how representability depends on system size and key model parameters, including number of determinant and model depth. By applying our benchmark protocol on Psiformer and Ferminet, we show that WF-Bench establish a unified dataset-driven framework for evaluating and comparing neural network wavefunctions and for guiding the design of future architectures.</p>"},{"id":"62771","en":"TriForces: Augmenting Atomistic GNNs for Transferable Representations","ko":"TriForces: 전이 가능한 Representation을 위한 Atomistic GNN 강화","authors":"Ali Ramlaoui, Alexandre Duval, Hannah Bull, Victor Schmidt, Hugues Talbot, Fragkiskos Malliaros, Joseph Musielewicz","pos":"#1113","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=dVgMUSGPN3","abs":"<p>Machine learning interatomic potentials (MLIPs) achieve excellent accuracy when trained on large Density Functional Theory (DFT) data. To be useful in practice, they must often be adapted to target chemistries using small and expensive task-specific datasets. However, MLIPs transfer inconsistently across domains, with representations that often loose accessible composition and structure information. To address this, we present TriForces, a model-agnostic three-stream framework that separates composition and structure information, combined with self-supervised learning to preserve transferable representations. TriForces improves performance on MatBench and QM9 over baselines without needing DFT labels and enables efficient similar structure retrieval through its learned latent space. On OMat24, in limited-data training regime, TriForces reduces energy MAE by 57\\% at 20K samples only and improves force MAE across sample sizes. We release pretrained TriForces variants across multiple MLIP architectures with code at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/triforces-063E.</p>","absKo":"<p>Machine learning interatomic potentials (MLIPs)는 대규모 Density Functional Theory (DFT) 데이터로 학습될 때 뛰어난 정확도를 달성한다. 실제로 유용하려면, 이들은 종종 작고 비용이 큰 task-specific dataset을 사용해 목표 chemistry에 적응되어야 한다. 그러나 MLIPs는 domain 간 transfer가 일관되지 않으며, representation이 접근 가능한 composition과 structure 정보를 종종 잃어버린다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 composition과 structure 정보를 분리하고 self-supervised learning을 결합하여 transferable representation을 보존하는 model-agnostic three-stream framework인 TriForces를 제안한다. TriForces는 DFT label 없이도 MatBench와 QM9에서 baseline보다 성능을 향상시키며, 학습된 latent space를 통해 효율적인 similar structure retrieval을 가능하게 한다. OMat24에서는 limited-data training regime에서 TriForces가 20K sample에서 energy MAE를 57\\% 줄이고 sample size 전반에 걸쳐 force MAE를 개선한다. 우리는 코드 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/triforces-063E 와 함께 여러 MLIP architecture에 걸친 pretrained TriForces variant를 공개한다.</p>"},{"id":"66586","en":"TINNs: Time-Induced Neural Networks for Solving Time-Dependent PDEs","ko":"TINNs: 시간 의존 PDE 풀이를 위한 시간 유도 신경망","authors":"Chen-Yang Dai, Che-Chia Chang, Te-Sheng Lin, Ming-Chih Lai, Chieh-Hsin Lai","pos":"#1114","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=2PFiFk3gWq","abs":"Physics-informed neural networks (PINNs) solve time-dependent partial differential equations (PDEs) by learning a mesh-free, differentiable solution that can be evaluated anywhere in space and time. However, standard space-time PINNs take time as an input but reuse a single network with shared weights across all times, forcing the same features to represent markedly different dynamics. This coupling degrades accuracy and can destabilize training when enforcing PDE, boundary, and initial constraints jointly. We propose *Time-Induced Neural Networks (TINNs)*, a novel architecture that parameterizes the network weights as a learned function of time, allowing the effective spatial representation to evolve over time while maintaining shared structure. The resulting formulation naturally yields a nonlinear least-squares problem, which we optimize efficiently using a Levenberg-Marquardt method. Experiments on various time-dependent PDEs show up to $4\\times$ improved accuracy and $10\\times$ faster convergence compared to PINNs and strong baselines."},{"id":"60675","en":"CoarseBind: Fast and Accurate Binding Affinity Prediction through Coarse Structural Representations","ko":"CoarseBind: 거친 구조 표현을 통한 빠르고 정확한 Binding Affinity Prediction","authors":"Matteo Rossi, Ryan Pederson, Miles Wang-Henderson, Benjamin Kaufman, Edward Williams, Carl Underkoffler, Owen Howell, Adrian Layer, Stephan Thaler, Narbe Mardirossian, John Parkhill","pos":"#1200","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=xlevHY3oJO","abs":"We present CoarseBind, a foundation model for protein-ligand structure and binding affinity prediction that achieves 26$\\times$ faster inference than state-of-the-art methods while improving affinity prediction accuracy by up to 20\\%. Current deep learning approaches to structure-based drug design rely on expensive all-atom diffusion to generate 3D coordinates, creating inference bottlenecks that render large-scale compound screening computationally intractable. We challenge this paradigm with the hypothesis: full all-atom resolution is unnecessary for accurate small molecule pose and binding affinity prediction. CoarseBind tests this hypothesis through a coarse pocket-level representation (protein C$_\\beta$ atoms and ligand heavy atoms only) within a multimodal architecture combining pretrained molecular encoders and ESM-2 protein embeddings that learns rich structural representations, which are used in a diffusion-free optimization module for pose generation and a binding affinity likelihood prediction module. On structure prediction benchmarks, CoarseBind matches diffusion-based baselines in ligand pose accuracy. For binding affinity, CoarseBind outperforms Boltz-2 by 16-20\\% in Pearson correlation on both a public benchmark (CASP16) and a diverse private dataset (18 assays). The affinity module also provides well-calibrated uncertainty estimates, addressing a critical gap in compound prioritization for drug discovery. Furthermore, this module enables a continual learning framework and a hedged batch selection strategy that, in simulated drug discovery cycles, achieves 6$\\times$ greater affinity improvement over greedy approaches.","absKo":"Protein-ligand structure와 binding affinity prediction을 위한 foundation model인 CoarseBind를 제시한다. CoarseBind는 state-of-the-art method보다 26$\\times$ 더 빠른 inference를 달성하면서 affinity prediction accuracy는 최대 20\\%까지 향상시킨다. 구조 기반 drug design에 대한 현재의 deep learning 접근은 3D coordinate 생성을 위해 비용이 큰 all-atom diffusion에 의존하여, 대규모 compound screening을 계산적으로 감당할 수 없게 만드는 inference bottleneck을 초래한다. 우리는 다음과 같은 가설로 이 패러다임에 도전한다: 정확한 small molecule pose와 binding affinity prediction에는 full all-atom resolution이 필요하지 않다. CoarseBind는 pretrained molecular encoder와 ESM-2 protein embedding을 결합한 multimodal architecture 안에서 coarse pocket-level representation(protein C$_\\beta$ atoms와 ligand heavy atom만 사용)을 통해 이 가설을 검증하며, 풍부한 structural representation을 학습한다. 이 representation은 pose generation을 위한 diffusion-free optimization module과 binding affinity likelihood prediction module에 사용된다. structure prediction benchmark에서 CoarseBind는 ligand pose accuracy 면에서 diffusion-based baseline과 동등한 성능을 보인다. binding affinity에서는 CoarseBind가 공개 benchmark(CASP16)와 다양한 private dataset(18 assays) 모두에서 Pearson correlation 기준으로 Boltz-2를 16-20\\% 능가한다. affinity module은 또한 잘 보정된 uncertainty estimate를 제공하여, drug discovery에서 compound prioritization의 중대한 공백을 메운다. 더 나아가, 이 모듈은 continual learning framework와 hedged batch selection strategy를 가능하게 하며, 시뮬레이션된 drug discovery cycle에서 greedy approach보다 6$\\times$ 더 큰 affinity improvement를 달성한다."},{"id":"62275","en":"Coupled Cluster con MoLe: Molecular Orbital Learning for Neural Wavefunctions","ko":"Coupled Cluster con MoLe: Neural Wavefunctions를 위한 Molecular Orbital Learning","authors":"Luca Anthony Thiede, Abdulrahman Aldossary, Andreas Burger, Jorge Campos-Gonzalez-Angulo, Alex Zook, Melisa Alkan, KOHEI NAKAJI, Jérôme F. Gonthier, Taylor Patti, Mohammad Vakili, Alan Aspuru-Guzik","pos":"#1201","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=i5QhkUCzJh","abs":"<p>Density functional theory (DFT) is the most widely used method for calculating molecular properties; however, its accuracy is often insufficient for quantitative predictions. Coupled cluster (CC) theory is the most successful method for achieving accuracy beyond DFT and predicting properties that closely align with experiment. It is known as the ``gold standard'' of quantum chemistry. Unfortunately, the high computational cost of CC limits its widespread applicability. In this work, we present the Molecular Orbital Learning Model (MoLe), an equivariant machine learning model that directly predicts CC's core mathematical objects, the excitation amplitudes, from the mean-field Hartree-Fock molecular orbitals as inputs. We test various aspects of our model and demonstrate its very high data efficiency and remarkable out-of-distribution generalization to larger molecules and off-equilibrium geometries, despite being trained only on small equilibrium geometries. Finally, we also examine its ability to reduce the number of cycles required to converge CC calculations. MoLe can set the foundations for high-accuracy wavefunction-based ML architectures to accelerate molecular design and complement force-field approaches.</p>","absKo":"<p>Density functional theory (DFT)는 분자 물성을 계산하는 데 가장 널리 사용되는 방법이지만, 정확도가 정량적 예측에는 종종 충분하지 않습니다. Coupled cluster (CC) 이론은 DFT를 넘어서는 정확도를 달성하고 실험과 밀접하게 일치하는 물성을 예측하는 데 가장 성공적인 방법입니다. 이는 quantum chemistry의 ``gold standard''로 알려져 있습니다. 안타깝게도 CC의 높은 계산 비용은 광범위한 활용을 제한합니다. 본 연구에서는 mean-field Hartree-Fock 분자 orbital을 입력으로 받아 CC의 핵심 수학적 객체인 excitation amplitude를 직접 예측하는 equivariant machine learning model인 Molecular Orbital Learning Model (MoLe)을 제안합니다. 우리는 다양한 측면에서 모델을 검증하고, 작은 equilibrium geometry에서만 학습되었음에도 매우 높은 data efficiency와 더 큰 분자 및 off-equilibrium geometry에 대한 놀라운 out-of-distribution generalization을 입증합니다. 마지막으로, CC 계산의 수렴에 필요한 cycle 수를 줄일 수 있는 능력도 살펴봅니다. MoLe는 molecular design을 가속하고 force-field 접근법을 보완할 수 있는 고정확도 wavefunction-based ML architecture의 기반을 마련할 수 있습니다.</p>"},{"id":"61873","en":"Cross-Chirality Generalization by Axial Vectors for Hetero-Chiral Protein-Peptide Interaction Design","ko":"Hetero-Chiral 단백질-펩타이드 상호작용 설계를 위한 Axial Vector 기반 Cross-Chirality Generalization","authors":"Ziyi Yang, Zitong Tian, Yinjun Jia, Tianyi Zhang, Jiqing Zheng, Hao Wang, Yubu Su, Juncai He, Lei Liu, Yanyan Lan","pos":"#1202","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=mAusAlRZ0a","abs":"<p>D-peptide binders targeting L-proteins have promising therapeutic potential. Despite rapid advances in machine learning-based target-conditioned peptide design, generating D-peptide binders remains largely unexplored. In this work, we show that by injecting axial features to E(3)-equivariant (polar) vector features, it is feasible to achieve cross-chirality generalization from homo-chiral (L-L) training data to hetero-chiral (D-L) design tasks. By implementing this method within a latent diffusion model, we achieved D-peptide binder design that not only outperforms existing tools in <em>in silico</em> benchmarks, but also demonstrates efficacy in wet-lab validation. To our knowledge, our approach represents the first experimentally validated AI generative model for the <em>de novo</em> design of D-peptide binders, offering new perspectives on handling chirality in protein design.</p>","absKo":"<p>L-protein을 표적으로 하는 D-peptide binder는 유망한 치료적 잠재력을 지닙니다. machine learning 기반 target-conditioned peptide design이 빠르게 발전하고 있음에도, D-peptide binder 생성은 여전히 충분히 탐구되지 않았습니다. 본 연구에서는 E(3)-equivariant한 (polar) vector feature에 axial feature를 주입함으로써, 동형키랄(homo-chiral) (L-L) training data에서 이형키랄(hetero-chiral) (D-L) design task로 cross-chirality generalization을 달성할 수 있음을 보입니다. 이 방법을 latent diffusion model에 구현하여, <em>in silico</em> benchmark에서 기존 도구들을 능가할 뿐 아니라 wet-lab validation에서도 효능을 입증하는 D-peptide binder design을 달성했습니다. 우리가 아는 한, 우리의 접근법은 D-peptide binder의 <em>de novo</em> 설계를 위한 최초의 실험 검증된 AI generative model로, protein design에서 chirality를 다루는 새로운 관점을 제시합니다.</p>"},{"id":"62602","en":"Efficient Prediction of SO(3)-Equivariant Hamiltonian Matrices via SO(2) Local Frames","ko":"SO(2) Local Frames로 SO(3)-Equivariant Hamiltonian Matrix의 효율적 예측","authors":"Haiyang Yu, Yuchao Lin, Xuan Zhang, Xiaofeng Qian, Shuiwang Ji","pos":"#1204","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=f9i6VLHT5v","abs":"<p>We consider the task of predicting Hamiltonian matrices to accelerate electronic structure calculations, which plays an important role in physics, chemistry, and materials science. Motivated by the inherent relationship between the off-diagonal blocks of the Hamiltonian matrix and the SO(2) local frame, we propose a novel and efficient network, called QHNetV2, that achieves global SO(3) equivariance without the costly SO(3) Clebsch–Gordan tensor products. This is achieved by introducing a set of new efficient and powerful SO(2)-equivariant operations and performing all off-diagonal feature updates and message passing within SO(2) local frames, thereby eliminating the need of SO(3) tensor products. Moreover, a continuous SO(2) tensor product is performed within the SO(2) local frame at each node to fuse node features. Extensive experiments on the large QH9 and MD17 datasets demonstrate that our model achieves superior performance across a wide range of molecular structures and trajectories, highlighting its strong generalization capability. The proposed SO(2) operations on SO(2) local frames offer a promising direction for scalable and symmetry-aware learning of electronic structures.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 전자 구조 계산을 가속화하기 위해 Hamiltonian matrix를 예측하는 과제를 고려한다. 이는 물리학, 화학, 재료과학에서 중요한 역할을 한다. Hamiltonian matrix의 off-diagonal block과 SO(2) local frame 사이의 내재적 관계에 착안하여, 우리는 비용이 큰 SO(3) Clebsch–Gordan tensor product 없이도 전역 SO(3) equivariance를 달성하는 QHNetV2라는 새롭고 효율적인 네트워크를 제안한다. 이는 새롭고 효율적이며 강력한 SO(2)-equivariant 연산 집합을 도입하고, 모든 off-diagonal feature update와 message passing을 SO(2) local frame 내부에서 수행함으로써 SO(3) tensor product의 필요를 제거하여 달성된다. 더 나아가, 각 노드의 SO(2) local frame 내부에서 continuous SO(2) tensor product를 수행하여 노드 특징을 융합한다. 대규모 QH9 및 MD17 데이터셋에서의 광범위한 실험은 우리 모델이 다양한 분자 구조와 trajectory 전반에서 우수한 성능을 보이며 강한 일반화 능력을 드러냄을 보여준다. SO(2) local frame 위의 제안된 SO(2) 연산은 전자 구조의 확장 가능하고 대칭성을 인식하는 학습을 위한 유망한 방향을 제시한다.</p>"},{"id":"63807","en":"From Basis to Basis: Gaussian Particle Representation for Interpretable PDE Operators","ko":"해석 가능한 PDE operator를 위한 basis-to-basis Gaussian particle representation","authors":"Zhihao LI, Yu Feng, Zhilu Lai, Wei Wang","pos":"#1205","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=TYswUgruqt","abs":"Learning PDE dynamics for fluids increasingly relies on neural operators and Transformer-based models, yet these approaches often lack interpretability and struggle with localized, high-frequency structures while incurring quadratic cost in spatial samples. We propose to represent fields with a \\emph{Gaussian basis}, where learned atoms carry explicit geometry (centers, anisotropic scales, weights) and form a compact, mesh-agnostic, directly visualizable state. Building on this representation, we introduce a \\emph{Gaussian Particle Operator} that acts \\emph{in modal space}: learned \\emph{Gaussian modal windows} perform a Petrov--Galerkin measurement, a \\emph{PG Gaussian Attention} effects global cross-scale coupling. This basis-to-basis design is resolution-agnostic and achieves near-linear complexity in $N$ for fixed modal budget, supporting irregular geometries and seamless 2D$\\to$3D extension. On standard PDE benchmarks and real datasets, our method attains state-of-the-art–competitive accuracy while providing intrinsic interpretability.","absKo":"유체에 대한 PDE dynamics를 학습하는 일은 점점 neural operator와 Transformer 기반 model에 의존하고 있지만, 이러한 접근법은 종종 해석 가능성이 부족하고 국소적이며 고주파적인 구조를 다루는 데 어려움을 겪는 동시에, spatial sample에 대해 quadratic cost를 유발한다. 우리는 field를 \\emph{Gaussian basis}로 표현할 것을 제안하며, 여기서 학습된 atom은 명시적 기하(중심, anisotropic scale, weight)를 지니고, 컴팩트하고 mesh에 구애받지 않으며 직접 시각화 가능한 상태를 형성한다. 이 표현을 바탕으로, 우리는 \\emph{Gaussian Particle Operator}를 도입한다. 이 연산자는 \\emph{modal space}에서 작동하며, 학습된 \\emph{Gaussian modal window}가 Petrov--Galerkin 측정을 수행하고, \\emph{PG Gaussian Attention}이 전역적인 cross-scale coupling을 가능하게 한다. 이러한 basis-to-basis 설계는 resolution-agnostic이며, 고정된 modal budget에서 N에 대해 거의 선형적인 복잡도를 달성하고, 불규칙한 geometry와 2D$\\to$3D의 매끄러운 확장을 지원한다. 표준 PDE benchmark와 실제 데이터셋에서, 우리의 방법은 intrinsic interpretability를 제공하면서도 state-of-the-art에 경쟁적인 정확도를 달성한다."},{"id":"63763","en":"JanusPipe: Efficient Pipeline Parallel Training for Machine Learning Interatomic Potentials","ko":"JanusPipe: Machine Learning Interatomic Potentials를 위한 효율적 Pipeline Parallel Training","authors":"Hongyu Wang, Weijian Liu, Mingzhen Li, Hongtao Xu, Yan Wang, Weile Jia, Guangming Tan","pos":"#1206","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=TxWbgnFYCr","abs":"Discovering atom-level phenomena requires molecular dynamics (MD) simulations with ab initio accuracy.  Machine learning interatomic potentials (MLIPs) enable stable, high-accuracy MD simulations, and their models exhibit scaling-law trends similar to large language models.  However, the lack of scalable and efficient distributed training systems for conservative MLIPs makes them difficult to scale.  This is because conservative MLIPs inherently follow a double-backward execution pattern, which involves computing gradients during the forward pass. This pattern creates a mismatch with existing distributed training systems, especially for pipeline parallelism. Therefore, we present JanusPipe, an efficient 3D-parallel (PP/DP/GP) training system tailored for conservative MLIPs.  It integrates SymFold to enable memory-efficient pipeline parallelism for conservative MLIPs, and WaveK to reduce pipeline bubbles by balancing the four-phase compute time. Experimental results on 32 GPUs show that JanusPipe improves throughput by $1.51\\times$ and $1.45\\times$ on average over 1F1B and Hanayo, respectively.","absKo":"원자 수준의 현상을 발견하려면 ab initio 정확도를 갖는 molecular dynamics (MD) 시뮬레이션이 필요하다. machine learning interatomic potentials (MLIPs)는 안정적이고 고정확도인 MD 시뮬레이션을 가능하게 하며, 그 모델은 large language model과 유사한 scaling-law 경향을 보인다. 그러나 conservative MLIP을 위한 확장 가능하고 효율적인 distributed training system이 부족해 이를 대규모로 확장하기 어렵다. 이는 conservative MLIP가 본질적으로 double-backward 실행 패턴을 따르기 때문인데, 이 패턴에서는 forward pass 동안 gradient를 계산해야 한다. 이 패턴은 기존 distributed training system, 특히 pipeline parallelism과 잘 맞지 않는다. 따라서 우리는 conservative MLIP에 특화된 효율적인 3D-parallel (PP/DP/GP) training system인 JanusPipe를 제안한다. JanusPipe는 conservative MLIP에 대해 memory-efficient pipeline parallelism을 가능하게 하는 SymFold와, 네 단계의 compute time을 균형화하여 pipeline bubble을 줄이는 WaveK를 통합한다. 32 GPUs에서의 실험 결과, JanusPipe는 1F1B와 Hanayo에 비해 각각 평균 $1.51\\times$와 $1.45\\times$의 throughput 향상을 보였다."},{"id":"63060","en":"LeakGFN: Robust Molecular Generation in Generative Flow Networks via Flow Decomposition","ko":"LeakGFN: Flow 분해를 통한 Generative Flow Network에서의 견고한 분자 생성","authors":"Hwanhee Kim, Seungyeon Choi, Sanghyun Park","pos":"#1207","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=aS5zkIyzpG","abs":"<p>Generative Flow Networks (GFlowNets) have emerged as a powerful framework for molecular generation, sampling diverse candidates proportionally to a reward function. However, the vast chemical space necessitates truncating trajectory length, forcing models to treat incomplete molecular fragments as terminal states alongside valid molecules. This conflation distorts the learned distribution by allocating probability mass to chemically meaningless states. We propose LeakGFN, a dual-head architecture that decomposes flow into two components: a chemical head modeling flow over the full chemical space, and a valid head estimating the fraction of flow reaching valid molecules within the truncation boundary. Through this decomposition, the valid head implicitly learns molecular reachability without explicit supervision. We prove that LeakGFN recovers the correct distribution over accessible molecules under mild assumptions. Experiments on five molecular optimization tasks demonstrate consistent improvements over flow matching baselines, achieving state-of-the-art performance on four out of five tasks. Our module integrates as a plug-and-play enhancement into existing frameworks, improving performance on both pocket-conditioned and multi-objective generation tasks.</p>","absKo":"<p>Generative Flow Networks (GFlowNets)는 보상 함수에 비례하도록 다양한 후보를 샘플링하면서 분자 생성에 강력한 프레임워크로 부상했다. 그러나 방대한 화학 공간 때문에 trajectory 길이를 잘라야 하며, 그 결과 모델은 유효한 분자와 함께 불완전한 분자 조각도 terminal state로 취급해야 한다. 이러한 혼동은 화학적으로 의미 없는 상태에 probability mass를 할당함으로써 학습된 분포를 왜곡한다. 우리는 flow를 두 구성요소로 분해하는 dual-head 아키텍처인 LeakGFN을 제안한다. 하나는 전체 화학 공간 위의 flow를 모델링하는 chemical head이고, 다른 하나는 truncation boundary 안에서 유효한 분자에 도달하는 flow의 비율을 추정하는 valid head이다. 이 분해를 통해 valid head는 명시적 supervision 없이도 분자 reachability를 암묵적으로 학습한다. 우리는 LeakGFN이 완만한 가정하에서 접근 가능한 분자들에 대한 올바른 분포를 복원함을 증명한다. 다섯 가지 분자 최적화 task 실험에서 flow matching baseline 대비 일관된 개선을 보였고, 다섯 task 중 네 개에서 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성했다. 이 모듈은 기존 프레임워크에 plug-and-play 향상으로 통합되며, pocket-conditioned generation과 multi-objective generation task 모두에서 성능을 개선한다.</p>"},{"id":"66655","en":"MUSA-PINN: Multi-scale Weak-form Physics-Informed Neural Networks for Fluid Flow in Complex Geometries","ko":"MUSA-PINN: 복잡 기하 내 유체 흐름을 위한 다중 스케일 약형식 Physics-Informed Neural Network","authors":"Weizheng Zhang, Xunjie Xie, Hao Pan, Xiaowei Duan, Bingteng Sun, Qiang Du, Lin Lu","pos":"#1208","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=1gYQX9L1cb","abs":"<p>While Physics-Informed Neural Networks (PINNs) offer a mesh-free approach to solving PDEs, standard point-wise residual minimization suffers from convergence pathologies in topologically complex domains like Triply Periodic Minimal Surfaces (TPMS). The locality bias of point-wise constraints fails to propagate global information through tortuous channels, causing unstable gradients and conservation violations. To address this, we propose the Multi-scale Weak-form PINN (MUSA-PINN), which reformulates PDE constraints as integral conservation laws over hierarchical spherical control volumes. We enforce continuity and momentum conservation via flux-balance residuals on control surfaces. Our method utilizes a three-scale subdomain strategy—comprising large volumes for long-range coupling, skeleton-aware meso-scale volumes aligned with transport pathways, and small volumes for local refinement—alongside a two-stage training schedule prioritizing continuity. Experiments on steady incompressible flow in TPMS geometries show MUSA-PINN outperforms state-of-the-art baselines, reducing relative errors by up to 93\\% and preserving mass conservation.</p>"},{"id":"65680","en":"Neural Minimum Weight Perfect Matching for Quantum Error Codes","ko":"양자 오류 코드를 위한 신경망 기반 최소 가중치 완전 매칭","authors":"Yotam Peled, David Zenati, Eliya Nachmani","pos":"#1209","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=BFX213mKfh","abs":"<p>Realizing the full potential of quantum computation requires Quantum Error Correction (QEC). QEC reduces error rates by encoding logical information across redundant physical qubits, enabling errors to be detected and corrected. A common decoder used for this task is Minimum Weight Perfect Matching (MWPM) a graph-based algorithm that relies on edge weights to identify the most likely error chains. In this work, we propose a data-driven decoder named Neural Minimum Weight Perfect Matching (NMWPM). Our decoder utilizes a hybrid architecture that integrates Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) to extract local syndrome features and Transformers to capture long-range global dependencies, which are then used to predict dynamic edge weights for the MWPM decoder. To facilitate training through the non-differentiable MWPM algorithm, we formulate a novel proxy loss function that enables end-to-end optimization.  Our findings on the toric code under depolarizing noise demonstrate thresholds of 17.9\\% and 10.95\\%, nearing the 18.9\\% and 11.0\\% maximum likelihood bounds, highlighting the advantage of hybrid decoders that combine the predictive capabilities of neural networks with the algorithmic structure of classical matching.</p>"},{"id":"63089","en":"Neural Quantum States in Mixed Precision","ko":"혼합 정밀도의 Neural Quantum State","authors":"Massimo Solinas, Agnes Valenti, Nawaf Bou-Rabee, Roeland Wiersema","pos":"#1210","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=aDLJNoseDH","abs":"<p>Scientific computing has long relied on double precision (64-bit floating point) arithmetic to guarantee accuracy in simulations of real-world phenomena. However, the growing availability of hardware accelerators such as Graphics Processing Units (GPUs) has made low-precision formats attractive due to their superior performance, reduced memory footprint, and improved energy efficiency.  In this work, we investigate the role of mixed-precision arithmetic in neural-network based Variational Monte Carlo (VMC), a widely used method for solving computationally otherwise intractable quantum many-body systems. We first derive general analytical bounds on the error introduced by reduced precision on Metropolis-Hastings MCMC, and then empirically validate these bounds  on the use-case of VMC. We demonstrate that significant portions of the algorithm, in particular, sampling the quantum state, can be executed in half precision without loss of accuracy. More broadly, this work provides a theoretical framework to assess the applicability of mixed-precision arithmetic in machine-learning approaches that rely on MCMC sampling. In the context of VMC,  we additionally demonstrate the practical effectiveness of mixed-precision strategies,  enabling more scalable and energy-efficient simulations of  quantum many-body systems.</p>","absKo":"과학 계산은 실제 현상을 시뮬레이션할 때 정확도를 보장하기 위해 오랫동안 double precision (64-bit floating point) 연산에 의존해 왔다. 그러나 Graphics Processing Units (GPUs)와 같은 hardware accelerator의 가용성이 커지면서, 우수한 성능, 더 작은 memory footprint, 향상된 energy efficiency 때문에 low-precision format이 매력적인 대안이 되었다. 이 연구에서는 계산적으로는 그 외에는 다루기 어려운 quantum many-body system을 푸는 데 널리 사용되는 neural-network 기반 Variational Monte Carlo (VMC)에서 mixed-precision arithmetic의 역할을 조사한다. 먼저 우리는 Metropolis-Hastings MCMC에 대해 reduced precision이 도입하는 error에 대한 일반적인 analytical bound를 유도하고, 이어서 VMC 사용 사례에서 이 bound를 실증적으로 검증한다. 우리는 알고리즘의 상당 부분, 특히 quantum state sampling은 정확도 손실 없이 half precision으로 실행할 수 있음을 보인다. 더 넓게는, 이 연구는 MCMC sampling에 의존하는 machine-learning 접근에서 mixed-precision arithmetic의 적용 가능성을 평가하기 위한 이론적 framework를 제공한다. VMC의 맥락에서 우리는 또한 mixed-precision 전략의 실용적 효과를 추가로 입증하여, quantum many-body system의 더 확장 가능하고 에너지 효율적인 시뮬레이션을 가능하게 한다.</p>"},{"id":"64181","en":"PFT: Phonon Fine-tuning for Machine Learned Interatomic Potentials","ko":"PFT: 기계 학습 원자간 퍼텐셜을 위한 포논 미세조정","authors":"Teddy Koker, Abhijeet Gangan, Mit Kotak, Jaime Marian, Tess Smidt","pos":"#1211","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=QC9S8gUOYc","abs":"<p>Many materials properties depend on higher-order derivatives of the potential energy surface, yet machine learned interatomic potentials (MLIPs) trained with a standard loss on energy, force, and stress errors can exhibit error in curvature, degrading the prediction of vibrational properties. We introduce phonon fine-tuning (PFT), which directly supervises second-order force constants of materials by matching MLIP energy Hessians to DFT-computed force constants from finite displacement phonon calculations. To scale to large supercells, PFT stochastically samples Hessian columns and computes the loss with a single Hessian-vector product. We also use a simple co-training scheme to incorporate upstream data to mitigate catastrophic forgetting. On the MDR Phonon benchmark, PFT improves Nequix MP by 55% on average across phonon thermodynamic properties and achieves state-of-the-art accuracy among models trained on Materials Project trajectories. PFT also generalizes to improve properties beyond second-derivatives, improving thermal conductivity predictions that rely on third-order derivatives of the potential energy.</p>","absKo":"<p>많은 materials property는 potential energy surface의 고차 미분에 의존하지만, energy, force, stress error에 대한 표준 loss로 학습된 machine learned interatomic potentials (MLIPs)는 curvature에서 error를 보일 수 있으며, 이는 vibrational property 예측을 저해한다. 우리는 phonon fine-tuning (PFT)을 도입하는데, 이는 finite displacement phonon calculation에서 얻은 DFT 계산 force constant에 MLIP energy Hessian을 맞추어 materials의 second-order force constant를 직접 supervision한다. 큰 supercell로 확장하기 위해, PFT는 Hessian column을 stochastic하게 샘플링하고 단일 Hessian-vector product로 loss를 계산한다. 또한 catastrophic forgetting을 완화하기 위해 upstream data를 통합하는 단순한 co-training scheme도 사용한다. MDR Phonon benchmark에서 PFT는 phonon thermodynamic property 전반에 걸쳐 Nequix MP를 평균 55% 향상시키고, Materials Project trajectory로 학습된 모델들 중 state-of-the-art accuracy를 달성한다. PFT는 또한 second-derivative를 넘어서는 property 개선으로 일반화되어, potential energy의 third-order derivative에 의존하는 thermal conductivity 예측도 향상시킨다.</p>"},{"id":"62198","en":"Plug-and-Play Benchmarking of Reinforcement Learning Algorithms for Large-Scale Flow Control","ko":"대규모 Flow Control을 위한 강화학습 알고리즘 Plug-and-Play Benchmarking","authors":"Jannis Becktepe, Aleksandra Franz, Nils Thuerey, Sebastian Peitz","pos":"#1212","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ilEooI8fK1","abs":"<p>Reinforcement learning (RL) has shown promising results in active flow control (AFC), yet progress in the field remains difficult to assess as existing studies rely on heterogeneous observation and actuation schemes, numerical setups, and evaluation protocols. Current AFC benchmarks attempt to address these issues but heavily rely on external computational fluid dynamics (CFD) solvers, are not fully differentiable, and provide limited 3D and multi-agent support. To overcome these limitations, we introduce FluidGym, the first standalone, fully differentiable benchmark suite for RL in AFC. Built entirely in PyTorch on top of the GPU-accelerated PICT solver, FluidGym runs in a single Python stack, requires no external CFD software, and provides standardized evaluation protocols. We present baseline results with PPO and SAC and release all environments, datasets, and trained models as public resources. FluidGym enables systematic comparison of control methods, establishes a scalable foundation for future research in learning-based flow control, and is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/fluidgym (anonymized mirror of our public repository).</p>","absKo":"<p>Reinforcement learning (RL)은 active flow control (AFC)에서 유망한 결과를 보여주었지만, 기존 연구들이 이질적인 observation 및 actuation scheme, numerical setup, evaluation protocol에 의존하기 때문에 이 분야의 진전을 평가하기가 어렵다. 현재의 AFC benchmark는 이러한 문제를 해결하려 하지만, 외부 computational fluid dynamics (CFD) solver에 크게 의존하고, 완전히 differentiable하지 않으며, 3D 및 multi-agent 지원이 제한적이다. 이러한 한계를 극복하기 위해, 우리는 AFC에서 RL을 위한 최초의 독립형, 완전 differentiable benchmark suite인 FluidGym을 도입한다. GPU 가속 PICT solver 위에 PyTorch로 완전히 구축된 FluidGym은 단일 Python stack에서 실행되며, 외부 CFD software를 필요로 하지 않고, 표준화된 evaluation protocol을 제공한다. 우리는 PPO와 SAC를 사용한 baseline 결과를 제시하고, 모든 environment, dataset, trained model을 공개 자원으로 배포한다. FluidGym은 제어 방법의 체계적인 비교를 가능하게 하고, learning-based flow control의 향후 연구를 위한 확장 가능한 기반을 확립하며, https://anonymous.4open.science/r/fluidgym (공개 저장소의 anonymized mirror)에서 이용할 수 있다.</p>"},{"id":"67172","en":"Position: The Inevitable Transition to Machine Learning in Quantum Chemistry","ko":"Position: 양자 화학에서 기계 학습으로의 불가피한 전환","authors":"Karen Sargsyan, Chao-Ping Hsu","pos":"#1213","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Mq1oTEIwp4","abs":"<p>Finding exact solutions to the quantum many-body problem is computationally intractable (QMA-hard). Traditional approximations for electrons in an atom or molecule---density functional theory and wavefunction methods---have been indispensable, but their development shows signs of saturation: DFT functionals have proliferated without converging toward the exact functional, and strong correlation remains largely unsolved after decades of effort. This position paper argues that machine learning represents the most promising path forward---not as a proof of logical necessity, but as a decision-theoretic argument: ML succeeds whether the underlying problems are truly hard or merely lack simple analytical solutions. We reframe recent traditional method development as ``hand-crafted machine learning'' that has exhausted the hypothesis space accessible to human intuition. Significant challenges remain, but these have clear research paths forward, unlike the fundamental barriers facing traditional approaches. ML-based approaches merit strategic priority in quantum chemistry's next phase.</p>"},{"id":"62457","en":"Protein Language Model Embeddings Improve Generalization of Implicit Transfer Operators","ko":"Protein Language Model 임베딩이 암시적 전이 연산자(Implicit Transfer Operators)의 일반화 성능을 개선","authors":"Panagiotis Antoniadis, Beatrice Pavesi, Ole Winther, Simon Olsson","pos":"#1214","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=gRzdGEtn3T","abs":"<p>Molecular dynamics (MD) is a central computational tool in physics, chemistry, and biology, enabling quantitative prediction of experimental observables as expectations over high-dimensional molecular distributions such as Boltzmann distributions and transition densities. However, conventional MD is fundamentally limited by the high computational cost required to generate independent samples. Generative molecular dynamics (GenMD) has recently emerged as an alternative, learning surrogates of molecular distributions either from data or through interaction with energy models. While these methods enable efficient sampling, their transferability across molecular systems is often limited. In this work, we show that  incorporating auxiliary sources of information can improve the data efficiency and generalization of transferable implicit transfer operators (TITO) for molecular dynamics. We find that coarse-grained TITO models are substantially more data-efficient than Boltzmann emulators, and that incorporating protein language model (PLM) embeddings further improves out-of-distribution generalization. Our approach, PLaTITO, achieves state-of-the-art performance on equilibrium sampling benchmarks for out-of-distribution protein systems, including fast-folding proteins. We further study the impact of additional conditioning signals---such as structural embeddings, temperature, and large-language-model-derived embeddings---on model performance.</p>","absKo":"<p>Molecular dynamics (MD)는 physics, chemistry, biology에서 중심적인 계산 도구로, Boltzmann distributions와 transition densities 같은 고차원 molecular distribution에 대한 expectation으로 실험 관측치를 정량적으로 예측할 수 있게 해준다. 그러나 conventional MD는 독립적인 sample을 생성하는 데 필요한 높은 계산 비용 때문에 본질적으로 제한된다. Generative molecular dynamics (GenMD)는 최근 데이터로부터 또는 energy model과의 interaction을 통해 molecular distribution의 surrogate를 학습하는 대안으로 등장했다. 이러한 방법들은 효율적인 sampling을 가능하게 하지만, 서로 다른 molecular system 간 transferability는 종종 제한적이다. 이 연구에서 우리는 auxiliary information source를 통합하면 molecular dynamics를 위한 transferable implicit transfer operator (TITO)의 data efficiency와 generalization을 향상시킬 수 있음을 보인다. 우리는 coarse-grained TITO model이 Boltzmann emulator보다 훨씬 더 data-efficient하며, protein language model (PLM) embedding을 추가하면 out-of-distribution generalization이 더 개선됨을 발견했다. 우리의 접근법인 PLaTITO는 fast-folding protein을 포함한 out-of-distribution protein system에 대한 equilibrium sampling benchmark에서 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성한다. 우리는 또한 structural embedding, temperature, large-language-model-derived embedding과 같은 추가 conditioning signal이 model performance에 미치는 영향도 함께 연구한다.</p>"},{"id":"61905","en":"ReCoG: Relational and Compact Context Graph Learning for Few-shot Molecular Property Prediction","ko":"ReCoG: 소수샷 분자 속성 예측을 위한 관계형·압축 컨텍스트 그래프 학습","authors":"Zeyu Wang, Xin Zheng, Yao Lu, Shanqing Yu, Qi Xuan, Shirui Pan","pos":"#1215","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=lmhLWnIVOk","abs":"<p>Few-shot molecular property prediction (FSMPP) is essential in drug discovery and materials design, where high-quality labeled data are often scarce and expensive to obtain. Despite the promising performance of existing methods, especially in the context-aware methods, they still face two-fold severe challenges with \\textit{insufficient structural context modeling} &amp;amp; \\textit{redundant auxiliary context learning}, leading to inadequate context graph exploration and ineffective information utilization for effective molecule representation learning.  To address these, in this paper, we propose a novel framework by learning on \\textbf{\\underline{Re}}lational  and \\textbf{\\underline{C}}ompact c\\textbf{\\underline{o}}ntext \\textbf{\\underline{G}}raph, named \\textbf{\\method}, to comprehensively exploit the context graph for expressive molecular property prediction. Specifically, the proposed \\method contains two core modules: a \\textbf{(1) cross-property relational learning module} to better model the structural and relational context information, and a \\textbf{(2) context graph information bottleneck module} to adaptively suppress irrelevant auxiliary signals for compact context information utilization, followed by a detailed theoretical demonstration regarding the importance of joint relational and compact knowledge extraction in context graphs. Extensive experiments across multiple datasets demonstrate that \\method consistently outperforms state-of-the-art methods, validating its superiority. Code is available at~\\url{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/ReCoG-main-40C7/}.</p>","absKo":"<p>Few-shot molecular property prediction(FSMPP)은 고품질 라벨 데이터가 종종 희소하고 획득 비용이 큰 약물 발견과 소재 설계에서 필수적이다. 기존 방법들, 특히 context-aware 방법들이 유망한 성능을 보임에도 불구하고, 여전히 \\textit{불충분한 structural context modeling}과 \\textit{중복적인 auxiliary context learning}이라는 두 가지 심각한 문제에 직면해 있으며, 이는 충분하지 않은 context graph exploration과 비효율적인 정보 활용으로 이어져 효과적인 molecule representation learning을 저해한다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 본 논문에서는 \\textbf{\\underline{Re}}lational 및 \\textbf{\\underline{C}}ompact c\\textbf{\\underline{o}}ntext \\textbf{\\underline{G}}raph에서 학습하는 새로운 프레임워크, 즉 \\textbf{\\method}를 제안하여, 표현력 있는 molecular property prediction을 위해 context graph를 포괄적으로 활용하고자 한다. 구체적으로, 제안하는 \\method는 두 개의 핵심 모듈로 구성된다: \\textbf{(1) cross-property relational learning module}은 structural 및 relational context 정보를 더 잘 모델링하고, \\textbf{(2) context graph information bottleneck module}은 관련 없는 보조 신호를 적응적으로 억제하여 compact한 context 정보 활용을 가능하게 한다. 또한 context graph에서 relational 및 compact knowledge를 함께 추출하는 것의 중요성에 대한 상세한 이론적 설명을 제시한다. 여러 데이터셋에 걸친 광범위한 실험은 \\method가 state-of-the-art 방법들을 일관되게 능가함을 보여주며, 그 우수성을 입증한다. 코드는 ~\\url{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/ReCoG-main-40C7/}에서 확인할 수 있다.</p>"},{"id":"64192","en":"Latent Diffusion Pretraining for Crystal Property Prediction","ko":"결정 물성 예측을 위한 잠재 Diffusion 사전학습","authors":"Shrimon Mukherjee, KISHALAY DAS, Partha Basuchowdhuri, Pawan Goyal, Niloy Ganguly","pos":"#2717","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Q5uj05ynu5","abs":"<p>Fast and accurate prediction of crystal properties is a central challenge in new materials design. Graph Neural Networks and transformer-based models have emerged as powerful tools for this task due to their ability to encode the local structural environment of atoms within a crystal. However, these models are data hungry and in practice labeled data for crystal properties are very scarce. Pretrain–finetuning strategies, particularly those based on diffusion models, have shown promise in addressing these limitations. In this work, we introduce a novel latent-diffusion based pretraining framework CrysLDNet designed to mitigate the data scarcity issue. Our approach integrates a Variational Autoencoder (VAE) with a diffusion model during the pretraining stage. The VAE encoder maps 3D crystal structures into a smooth latent space, within which the diffusion process is applied. This latent diffusion pretraining enables the graph encoder to effectively capture structural and chemical semantics from large-scale unlabeled data, which can then be finetuned for specific property prediction tasks. Comprehensive experiments on popular DFT datasets for property prediction reveal that CrysLDNet significantly outperforms both training-from-scratch and pretrained baselines, with improvements of 4.26% and 4.90% on JARVIS and MP datasets. Additionally, the learned representations remain robust under sparse data conditions and are expressive enough to correct DFT errors when finetuned with limited experimental data.</p>","absKo":"<p>결정 구조의 crystal property를 빠르고 정확하게 예측하는 것은 새로운 소재 설계의 핵심 과제이다. Graph Neural Network와 transformer 기반 모델은 crystal 내 원자의 local structural environment를 인코딩할 수 있다는 점에서 이 과제에 강력한 도구로 부상했다. 그러나 이러한 모델은 data hunger가 크며, 실제로 crystal property에 대한 labeled data는 매우 부족하다. 특히 diffusion model에 기반한 pretrain–finetuning 전략은 이러한 한계를 해결하는 유망한 방법으로 주목받아 왔다. 본 연구에서는 데이터 부족 문제를 완화하도록 설계된 새로운 latent-diffusion 기반 pretraining framework인 CrysLDNet을 소개한다. 우리의 접근법은 pretraining 단계에서 Variational Autoencoder(VAE)와 diffusion model을 통합한다. VAE encoder는 3D crystal structure를 매끄러운 latent space로 매핑하고, 그 공간에서 diffusion process가 적용된다. 이러한 latent diffusion pretraining은 graph encoder가 대규모 unlabeled data로부터 structural 및 chemical semantic을 효과적으로 포착하도록 하며, 이후 특정 property prediction task에 대해 finetune할 수 있다. property prediction을 위한 널리 쓰이는 DFT dataset에서 수행한 포괄적 실험은 CrysLDNet이 from-scratch training과 pretrained baseline 모두를 유의미하게 능가함을 보여주며, JARVIS와 MP dataset에서 각각 4.26%와 4.90%의 향상을 달성했다. 또한 학습된 representation은 sparse data 조건에서도 견고하게 유지되며, 제한된 experimental data로 finetuning할 경우 DFT error를 보정할 만큼 충분히 expressive하다.</p>"},{"id":"63932","en":"Demystifying Multimodal Biomolecular Co-design With Intrinsic Geodesic Coupling","ko":"내재적 geodesic coupling을 통한 멀티모달 biomolecular co-design 해명","authors":"Keyue Qiu, Xintong Wang, Zhilong Zhang, Hao Zhou, Wei-Ying Ma","pos":"#3914","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=SSoOP9ia5t","abs":"<p>Biomolecules such as proteins and small-molecule ligands play a central role in biological systems, arising from the tight interplay between sequence and three-dimensional structure. Recent generative models for biomolecular co-design aim to capture this interplay by jointly modeling coupled modalities. However, existing approaches largely adopt a parallel execution of marginal generative processes, implicitly enforcing fixed synchronous coupling. We argue that a critical but overlooked degree of freedom lies in how these marginal processes are \\emph{temporally coupled} during training and generation, where inappropriate coupling can introduce high-variance supervision and inconsistent intermediate states, affecting modality consistency. To address this, we introduce GeoCoupling, a systematic framework that optimizes for temporal couplings between heterogeneous modalities. Empirical results across structure-based drug design and unconditional protein design demonstrate the learned couplings consistently outperform synchronous and randomly coupled baselines, yielding biomolecules with improved physical validity and diversity.</p>","absKo":"<p>protein과 small-molecule ligand 같은 biomolecule은 sequence와 three-dimensional structure의 긴밀한 상호작용에서 비롯되며, 생물학적 시스템에서 핵심적인 역할을 한다. 최근 biomolecular co-design을 위한 generative model은 결합된 modality를 jointly model하여 이러한 상호작용을 포착하고자 한다. 그러나 기존 접근은 주로 marginal generative process의 parallel execution을 채택해, 고정된 synchronous coupling을 암묵적으로 강제한다. 우리는 중요한데도 간과된 자유도 하나가 training과 generation 동안 이러한 marginal process가 어떻게 \\emph{temporally coupled}되는가에 있다고 주장한다. 부적절한 coupling은 고분산 supervision과 일관성 없는 intermediate state를 유발하여 modality consistency에 영향을 줄 수 있다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 이질적 modality 간 temporal coupling을 최적화하는 체계적 framework인 GeoCoupling을 도입한다. structure-based drug design과 unconditional protein design 전반의 실험 결과, 학습된 coupling은 synchronous 및 random coupling baseline보다 일관되게 우수했으며, 더 나은 physical validity와 다양성을 가진 biomolecule을 생성했다.</p>"},{"id":"62022","en":"Inference-time optimization for experiment-grounded protein ensemble generation","ko":"실험 기반 protein ensemble 생성의 추론 시점 최적화","authors":"Sai Advaith Maddipatla, Anar Rzayev, Marco Pegoraro, Ailie Marx, Martin Pacesa, Paul Schanda, Sanketh Vedula, Alexander Bronstein","pos":"#613","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=kbhIfLokFn","abs":"<p>Protein function relies on dynamic conformational ensembles, yet current generative models like AlphaFold3 (AF3) often fail to produce ensembles that match experimental data. Recent experiment-guided generators attempt to address this by steering the reverse diffusion process. However, these methods are limited by fixed sampling horizons and sensitivity to initialization, often yielding thermodynamically implausible results.  We introduce a general inference-time optimization framework to solve these challenges. First, we optimize over latent representations to maximize ensemble log-likelihood, rather than perturbing structures post hoc. This approach eliminates dependence on diffusion length, removes initialization bias, and easily incorporates external constraints. Second, we present novel sampling schemes for drawing Boltzmann-weighted ensembles. By combining structural priors from AF3 with force-field–based priors, we sample from their product distribution while balancing experimental likelihoods.  Our results show that this framework consistently outperforms state-of-the-art guidance, improving diversity, physical energy, and agreement with data in X-ray crystallography and NMR, sometimes fitting the experimental data better than deposited PDB structures. Finally, inference-time optimization experiments maximizing iPTM scores reveal that perturbing MSA embeddings can artificially inflate model confidence. This exposes a vulnerability in current design metrics, whose mitigation could offer a pathway to reduce false discovery rates in binder engineering.</p>","absKo":"<p>Protein function은 dynamic conformational ensembles에 의존하지만, AlphaFold3(AF3) 같은 현재의 generative model들은 실험 데이터와 맞는 ensemble을 생성하는 데 종종 실패한다. 최근의 experiment-guided generator들은 reverse diffusion process를 steering하여 이를 해결하려고 시도한다. 그러나 이러한 방법은 고정된 sampling horizon과 initialization에 대한 민감성에 의해 제한되며, 종종 thermodynamically implausible한 결과를 낳는다. 우리는 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위한 일반적인 inference-time optimization framework를 제안한다. 첫째, 구조를 사후적으로 perturb하는 대신 latent representation을 최적화하여 ensemble log-likelihood를 최대화한다. 이 접근은 diffusion length에 대한 의존성을 제거하고, initialization bias를 없애며, 외부 제약도 쉽게 통합할 수 있다. 둘째, Boltzmann-weighted ensemble을 샘플링하기 위한 새로운 sampling scheme을 제시한다. AF3의 structural prior와 force-field 기반 prior를 결합함으로써, experimental likelihood를 균형 있게 맞추면서 이들의 product distribution에서 샘플링한다. 우리의 결과는 이 framework가 X-ray crystallography와 NMR에서 다양성, 물리적 에너지, 데이터와의 일치도 모두를 향상시키며, 때로는 deposited PDB structure보다 experimental data에 더 잘 맞추면서 state-of-the-art guidance를 일관되게 능가함을 보여준다. 마지막으로, iPTM score를 최대화하는 inference-time optimization 실험은 MSA embedding을 perturb하면 model confidence를 인위적으로 부풀릴 수 있음을 드러낸다. 이는 현재의 design metric에 취약점이 있음을 보여주며, 이를 완화하는 것은 binder engineering에서 false discovery rate를 줄이는 경로가 될 수 있다.</p>"},{"id":"65934","en":"Learning Situated Awareness in the Real World","ko":"실세계에서의 상황 인식 학습","authors":"Chuhan Li, Rilyn Han, Joy Hsu, Yongyuan Liang, Rajiv Dhawan, Jiajun Wu, Ming-Hsuan Yang, Xin (Eric) Wang","pos":"#4309","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=8lwrYjv6r7","abs":"<p>A core aspect of human perception is <em>situated awareness</em>, the ability to relate ourselves to the surrounding physical environment and reason over possible actions in context. However, most existing benchmarks for multimodal foundation models (MFMs) emphasize <strong>environment-centric</strong> spatial relations (relations among objects in a scene), while largely overlooking <strong>observer-centric</strong> relationships that require reasoning relative to agent's viewpoint, pose, and motion. To bridge this gap, we introduce SAW-Bench (<strong>S</strong>ituated <strong>A</strong>wareness in the Real <strong>W</strong>orld), a novel benchmark for evaluating egocentric situated awareness using real-world videos. SAW-Bench comprises 786 self-recorded videos captured with Ray-Ban Meta (Gen 2) smart glasses spanning diverse indoor and outdoor environments, and over 2071 <em>human-annotated</em> question-answer pairs. It probes a model’s observer–environment understanding with <em>six</em> different awareness tasks. Our comprehensive evaluation reveals a human-model performance gap of 31.97%, even with the best-performing MFM, Gemini 3 Flash. Beyond this gap, our in-depth analysis uncovers several notable findings; for example, while models can exploit partial geometric cues in egocentric videos, they often fail to infer a coherent camera geometry, leading to systematic spatial reasoning errors. We position SAW-Bench as a benchmark for situated spatial intelligence, moving beyond passive observation to understanding physically grounded, observer-centric dynamics.</p>"},{"id":"66201","en":"Coloring the Noise: Adversarial Sobolev Alignment for Faithful Image Super Resolution","ko":"노이즈에 색을 입히다: 충실한 이미지 초해상도를 위한 적대적 Sobolev 정렬","authors":"Hongbo Wang, Huaibo Huang, Pin Wang, Jinhua Hao, Chao Zhou, Ran He","pos":"#1100","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=5p36n5cMJy","abs":"<p>Generative priors in Image Super-Resolution (SR) often compromise faithful restoration, we attribute this limitation to a fundamental spectral misalignment between isotropic objectives and the intrinsic natural image manifold. While Direct Preference Optimization offers a path to alignment, its reliance on spectrally flat Gaussian noise fails to distinguish authentic high-frequency details from hallucinations. To bridge this geometric gap, we propose ASASR, a theoretically grounded framework that recasts the generative flow into a Sobolev-induced Riemannian geometry by explicitly coloring the noise transition kernel to mirror natural spectral decay. Driving this geometric alignment, we integrate a parametric adversary grounded in the Riesz Representation Theorem, which synthesizes targeted negative samples equivalent to worst-case Sobolev gradients to direct optimization along the tangent space of plausible structural failures.  Extensive evaluations demonstrate that ASASR outperforms leading generative baselines, particularly in preserving spectral consistency and structural fidelity, offering a robust solution that effectively mitigates artifacts.</p>"},{"id":"64070","en":"T-Edit: Triple-Branch Diffusion Anchoring for Consistent Editing","ko":"T-Edit: 일관된 편집을 위한 삼중 분기 Diffusion 앵커링","authors":"Linsong Shan, Laurence Yang, Zecan Yang, Shijie Lian, lv lv, Qilin Yang","pos":"#4417","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=RBE1rgYl39","abs":"<p>While Multimodal Diffusion Transformers (MMDiTs) have achieved remarkable success in high-fidelity generation, maintaining semantic faithfulness and structural consistency during the image editing process remains a fundamental challenge. DiT-based editing is primarily limited by cumulative drift and semantic leakage induced by new textual conditions. To address these challenges, we propose T-Edit, a training-free framework that formalizes consistent editing as a trajectory anchoring process. T-Edit explicitly decouples the inversion, reconstruction, and editing trajectories, leveraging the reconstruction branch as a structural reference to achieve real-time compensation for deviations in the latent manifold. To further reveal the internal regulation mechanism of DiTs, we analyze the spatio-temporal heterogeneity of their layer-wise structural sensitivity and accordingly propose a Dynamic Vital Layer (DVL) localization mechanism based on information energy. Furthermore, addressing the asymmetry of textual perturbations in the frequency domain distribution, we introduce a frequency-aware strategy based on tensor Singular Value Decomposition (t-SVD) to anchor (TA) high-rank structural components. Experiments show that T-Edit achieves state-of-the-art performance in both semantic alignment and structural fidelity, and can be seamlessly extended to multi-step editing and video scenarios, providing a new perspective for understanding and controlling the internal stability of DiTs.</p>","absKo":"<p>Multimodal Diffusion Transformer(MMDiT)는 고충실도 생성에서 놀라운 성공을 거두었지만, image editing 과정에서 semantic faithfulness와 structural consistency를 유지하는 것은 여전히 근본적인 과제로 남아 있다. DiT 기반 editing은 주로 새로운 textual condition에 의해 유발되는 누적 drift와 semantic leakage에 의해 제한된다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해 우리는 consistent editing을 trajectory anchoring process로 정식화하는 training-free framework인 T-Edit를 제안한다. T-Edit는 inversion, reconstruction, editing trajectory를 명시적으로 분리하고, reconstruction branch를 structural reference로 활용하여 latent manifold에서의 deviation을 실시간으로 보정한다. DiT의 내부 regulation mechanism을 더 잘 드러내기 위해, 우리는 layer-wise structural sensitivity의 spatio-temporal heterogeneity를 분석하고, 이에 따라 information energy를 기반으로 하는 Dynamic Vital Layer(DVL) localization mechanism을 제안한다. 더 나아가, frequency domain 분포에서 textual perturbation의 비대칭성을 고려하여, tensor Singular Value Decomposition(t-SVD)을 기반으로 높은 rank의 structural component를 anchor하는( TA ) frequency-aware 전략을 도입한다. 실험 결과, T-Edit는 semantic alignment와 structural fidelity 모두에서 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성하며, multi-step editing과 video scenario로도 매끄럽게 확장될 수 있어, DiT의 내부 안정성을 이해하고 제어하는 새로운 관점을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"63174","en":"ImpText: A Benchmark and Tool-Augmented Framework for Implicit Text Reasoning","ko":"ImpText: 암시적 텍스트 추론을 위한 벤치마크 및 도구 증강 프레임워크","authors":"Litao Guo, Jinsong Zhou, Shuaibo Li, Man CHEN, Xinli Xu, Zixin Zhang, Harold Haodong Chen, YINGCONG CHEN","pos":"#4601","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ZPJRm2K3oe","abs":"<p>Multimodal Large Language Models (MLLMs) have demonstrated exceptional proficiency in standard text extraction, but they encounter significant challenges when confronting real-world implicit text. Such content typically contains malicious information, intentionally concealed through physical deformation, visual camouflage, or cognitive suggestion. These concealment techniques circumvent content moderation systems and pose severe risks to user safety. To bridge the research gap in text recognition under real-world adversarial scenarios, we define the task of Implicit Text Reasoning and introduce ImpText-Bench, a meticulously constructed benchmark. Extensive evaluations on this benchmark reveal significant vulnerability in current systems; even advanced proprietary models achieve a maximum Text Match Score of only 35.79\\%. In response, we propose ImpText-Reader, a tool-augmented framework. It employs a three-stage training strategy utilizing capability-boundary data to collaboratively optimize tool selection and semantic reasoning, thereby effectively extracting hidden text. Extensive experiments demonstrate that our approach achieves SOTA performance, significantly enhancing model robustness in adversarial environments.</p>","absKo":"<p>Multimodal Large Language Models(MLLMs)는 표준 text extraction에서는 탁월한 성능을 보여주었지만, 실제 세계의 implicit text를 다룰 때는 심각한 도전에 직면한다. 이러한 content는 일반적으로 물리적 변형, visual camouflage, cognitive suggestion을 통해 의도적으로 숨겨진 악성 정보를 포함한다. 이러한 은닉 기법은 content moderation system을 우회하며 사용자 안전에 중대한 위험을 초래한다. 실제 adversarial scenario에서의 text recognition 연구 공백을 메우기 위해, 우리는 Implicit Text Reasoning task를 정의하고 정교하게 구성한 benchmark인 ImpText-Bench를 소개한다. 이 benchmark에 대한 광범위한 평가는 현재 시스템의 상당한 취약성을 드러내며, 고급 proprietary model조차 최대 Text Match Score가 35.79\\%에 불과하다. 이에 대응하여, 우리는 tool-augmented framework인 ImpText-Reader를 제안한다. 이는 capability-boundary data를 활용한 3단계 training strategy를 사용하여 tool selection과 semantic reasoning을 공동으로 최적화함으로써, 숨겨진 text를 효과적으로 추출한다. 광범위한 실험은 우리의 접근법이 SOTA performance를 달성하고 adversarial environment에서 model robustness를 크게 향상시킴을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"60836","en":"From Correspondence to Actions: Human-Like Multi-Image Spatial Reasoning in Multi-modal Large Language Models","ko":"대응에서 행동으로: Multi-modal Large Language Model의 인간형 다중 이미지 공간 추론","authors":"Masanari Oi, Koki Maeda, Ryuto Koike, Daisuke Oba, Nakamasa Inoue, Naoaki Okazaki","pos":"#1010","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=wCQEvBldlz","abs":"<p>While multimodal large language models (MLLMs) have made substantial progress in single-image spatial reasoning, multi-image spatial reasoning, which requires integration of information from multiple viewpoints, remains challenging. Cognitive studies suggest that humans address such tasks through two mechanisms: <em>cross-view correspondence</em>, which identifies regions across different views that correspond to the same physical locations, and <em>stepwise viewpoint transformation</em>, which composes relative viewpoint changes sequentially. However, existing studies incorporate these mechanisms only partially and often implicitly, without explicit supervision for both. We propose Human-Aware Training for Cross-view correspondence and viewpoint cHange (HATCH), a training framework with two complementary objectives: (1) Patch-Level Spatial Alignment, which encourages patch representations to align across views for spatially corresponding regions, and (2)  Action-then-Answer Reasoning, which requires the model to generate explicit viewpoint transition actions before predicting the final answer. Experiments on three benchmarks demonstrate that \\method consistently outperforms baselines of comparable size by a clear margin and achieves competitive results against much larger models, while preserving single-image reasoning capabilities.</p>","absKo":"<p>multimodal large language models(MLLMs)는 단일 이미지 spatial reasoning에서는 큰 진전을 이루었지만, 여러 시점의 정보를 통합해야 하는 multi-image spatial reasoning은 여전히 어렵다. 인지 연구는 인간이 이러한 과제를 두 가지 메커니즘으로 해결한다고 시사한다. 하나는 서로 다른 뷰에서 같은 물리적 위치에 대응하는 영역을 식별하는 <em>cross-view correspondence</em>이고, 다른 하나는 상대적인 viewpoint 변화들을 순차적으로 구성하는 <em>stepwise viewpoint transformation</em>이다. 그러나 기존 연구는 이들 메커니즘을 부분적으로만, 그리고 종종 암묵적으로 통합했을 뿐, 둘 모두에 대한 명시적 supervision은 제공하지 않았다. 우리는 Human-Aware Training for Cross-view correspondence and viewpoint cHange(HATCH)를 제안한다. 이는 두 가지 상보적 objective를 갖는 training framework이다. (1) Patch-Level Spatial Alignment는 spatially corresponding region에 대해 뷰 간 patch representation이 정렬되도록 유도하고, (2) Action-then-Answer Reasoning은 최종 답을 예측하기 전에 명시적인 viewpoint transition action을 생성하도록 모델에 요구한다. 세 개의 benchmark에서 수행한 실험은 \\method가 일관되게 동급 크기의 baseline을 분명한 차이로 능가하고, 훨씬 더 큰 model과도 경쟁력 있는 결과를 달성하면서 단일 이미지 추론 능력은 유지함을 보여 준다.</p>"},{"id":"63416","en":"ManiSoft: Towards Vision-Language Manipulation for Soft Robotics","ko":"ManiSoft: 소프트 로보틱스를 위한 Vision-Language 조작을 향하여","authors":"Ziyu Wei, Luting Wang, Chen GAO, Li Wen, Si Liu","pos":"#4602","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=XMO8lp4I2n","abs":"Most existing vision-language manipulation research targets rigid robotic arms, whose fixed morphology limits adaptability in cluttered or confined spaces.  Soft robotic arms offer an appealing alternative due to their deformability, but confront challenges such as unreliable proprioception and distributed low-level actuation. To investigate these challenges, we introduce ManiSoft, a benchmark for vision-language manipulation with soft arms.  \\ManiSoft{} features a tailored simulator that couples realistic soft-body dynamics with contact-rich interactions via an elastic force constraint. On this basis, ManiSoft defines four tasks, each highlighting distinct aspects of deformable control, from basic end-effector coordination to obstacle avoidance. To support policy training and evaluation, ManiSoft includes an automated pipeline that generates $6{,}300$ diverse scenes and corresponding expert trajectories. To produce high-quality trajectories at scale, we first employ a high-level planner to decompose each task into a sequence of waypoints, followed by a low-level reinforcement learning policy that generates torque commands to track waypoints. Benchmarking three representative policy models shows relatively promising results in clean scenes but substantial performance drop under randomization.  Visualization analysis indicates that failures stem primarily from inaccurate visual estimation of proprioceptive state and limited exploitation of deformability for adaptive obstacle avoiding. We anticipate ManiSoft to serve as a valuable testbed, bridging the gap between rigid and soft arms in the context of vision-language manipulation.","absKo":"대부분의 기존 vision-language manipulation 연구는 강체 로봇 팔을 대상으로 하며, 이들의 고정된 morphology는 cluttered하거나 confined된 공간에서의 적응성을 제한한다. Soft robotic arm은 변형 가능성 때문에 매력적인 대안이지만, 신뢰하기 어려운 proprioception과 분산된 low-level actuation 같은 문제에 직면한다. 이러한 문제를 조사하기 위해, 우리는 soft arm을 위한 vision-language manipulation benchmark인 ManiSoft를 소개한다. \\ManiSoft{}는 탄성 force constraint를 통해 현실적인 soft-body dynamics와 contact-rich interaction을 결합한 맞춤형 simulator를 특징으로 한다. 이를 바탕으로 ManiSoft는 basic end-effector coordination부터 obstacle avoidance에 이르기까지 변형 제어의 서로 다른 측면을 강조하는 네 가지 task를 정의한다. policy training과 evaluation을 지원하기 위해, ManiSoft는 $6{,}300$개의 다양한 scene과 대응하는 expert trajectory를 생성하는 자동화 pipeline을 포함한다. 대규모로 고품질 trajectory를 생성하기 위해, 우리는 먼저 high-level planner를 사용해 각 task를 waypoint sequence로 분해하고, 이어서 waypoint를 추종하는 torque command를 생성하는 low-level reinforcement learning policy를 사용한다. 세 개의 대표적인 policy model에 대한 benchmark 결과는 깨끗한 scene에서는 비교적 유망하지만, randomization 하에서는 성능이 크게 저하됨을 보여준다. 시각화 분석은 실패가 주로 proprioceptive state의 부정확한 visual estimation과 적응적 obstacle avoiding을 위한 deformability 활용의 제한에서 비롯됨을 시사한다. 우리는 ManiSoft가 vision-language manipulation 맥락에서 rigid arm과 soft arm 사이의 간극을 메우는 유용한 testbed로 기능하리라 기대한다.</p>"},{"id":"62143","en":"DiffThinker: Towards Generative Multimodal Reasoning with Diffusion Models","ko":"DiffThinker: Diffusion Model을 활용한 생성적 멀티모달 추론을 향해","authors":"Zefeng He, Xiaoye Qu, Yafu Li, Tong Zhu, Qipeng Guo, Muxin Fu, Siyuan Huang, Yu Cheng","pos":"#1002","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=jQ2DRkSir0","abs":"<p>While recent Multimodal Large Language Models (MLLMs) have attained significant strides in multimodal reasoning, their reasoning processes remain predominantly text-centric and fail to visualize and track intermediate visual states during the reasoning process, leading to suboptimal performance in complex long-horizon, vision-centric tasks.  Moving beyond the constraints of text-centric reasoning, we establish Generative Multimodal Reasoning as a novel paradigm and introduce DiffThinker, a diffusion-based reasoning framework. Conceptually, DiffThinker reformulates multimodal reasoning as a native generative image-to-image task, where the iterative denoising trajectory naturally serves as a visual reasoning path. This enables the model to track the evolution of visual information throughout the reasoning process. We perform a systematic comparison between DiffThinker and MLLMs, providing the first in-depth investigation into the intrinsic characteristics of this paradigm, revealing four core properties: efficiency, controllability, native parallelism, and collaboration. Extensive experiments across  seven tasks demonstrate that DiffThinker significantly outperforms leading closed-source models, including GPT-5 (+314.2%) and Gemini-3-Flash (+111.6%), as well as the fine-tuned Qwen3-VL-32B baseline (+39.0%), highlighting Generative Multimodal Reasoning as a promising approach for vision-centric reasoning.</p>","absKo":"<p>최근의 Multimodal Large Language Models (MLLMs)가 multimodal reasoning에서 상당한 진전을 이루었지만, 그 reasoning process는 여전히 주로 text-centric하며 reasoning 과정 중 중간 visual state를 시각화하고 추적하지 못해, 복잡한 long-horizon vision-centric task에서 최적 이하의 성능을 보인다. text-centric reasoning의 제약을 넘어, 우리는 Generative Multimodal Reasoning을 새로운 패러다임으로 정립하고 diffusion-based reasoning framework인 DiffThinker를 소개한다. 개념적으로 DiffThinker는 multimodal reasoning을 native generative image-to-image task로 재정의하며, 이때 iterative denoising trajectory는 자연스럽게 visual reasoning path로 작동한다. 이를 통해 모델은 reasoning process 전반에 걸쳐 visual information의 변화를 추적할 수 있다. 우리는 DiffThinker와 MLLMs를 체계적으로 비교하여, 이 패러다임의 내재적 특성에 대한 최초의 심층 조사를 제시하고, 효율성, 제어 가능성, native parallelism, collaboration이라는 네 가지 핵심 속성을 밝혔다. 7개 task에 걸친 광범위한 실험은 DiffThinker가 GPT-5 (+314.2%)와 Gemini-3-Flash (+111.6%)를 비롯한 주요 closed-source model은 물론 fine-tuned Qwen3-VL-32B baseline (+39.0%)보다도 현저히 우수함을 보여주며, Generative Multimodal Reasoning이 vision-centric reasoning을 위한 유망한 접근법임을 강조한다.</p>"},{"id":"61751","en":"Divide and Conquer: Reliable Multi-View Evidential Learning for Deepfake Detection","ko":"Divide and Conquer: Deepfake 탐지를 위한 신뢰 가능한 Multi-View Evidential Learning","authors":"Xiaolu Kang, Zhongyuan Wang, Baojin Huang, Jikang Cheng, Zhanhe Lei, Gang Wu, Qin Zou, Qian Wang","pos":"#1003","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=nETGpbMtcZ","abs":"<p>With the evolution of generative models, deepfakes have achieved near-perfect semantic realism, leaving forensic traces only in subtle structural anomalies. However, existing single-view paradigms often fail to generalize, as dominant semantic features overwhelm subtle artifact cues within entangled representations. This imbalance leads to overconfident yet brittle predictions—a phenomenon we term the Semantic Masking Effect.   To address this challenge, we propose \\Reliable Multi-View Evidential Learning for Deepfake Detection} under a \"Divide-and-Conquer\" strategy.    In the \"Divide\" phase, we employ Geometric View Purification to decompose the entangled representation space through principled geometric projection. This process suppresses semantic interference within artifact-sensitive representations, forming the foundation for independent semantic and artifact views.    In the \"Conquer\" phase, we leverage Uncertainty-Aware Evidential Learning to synthesize these distinct views. By explicitly modeling the \"epistemic conflict\" between semantic and artifact cues, this mechanism provides calibrated uncertainty estimates instead of forcing rigid deterministic decisions.   Extensive experiments across multiple benchmarks demonstrate that our method consistently outperforms existing approaches in generalization performance, while providing reliable uncertainty estimation for trustworthy deepfake detection.</p>","absKo":"<p>생성 모델의 진화와 함께 deepfake는 거의 완벽한 semantic realism에 도달했으며, forensic trace는 미세한 structural anomaly에만 남아 있다. 그러나 기존의 single-view paradigm은 entangled representation 내에서 지배적인 semantic feature가 미세한 artifact cue를 압도하기 때문에 일반화에 실패하는 경우가 많다. 이러한 불균형은 과도하게 확신하지만 취약한 예측을 초래하는데, 우리는 이를 Semantic Masking Effect라고 부른다.   이 과제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 \\Reliable Multi-View Evidential Learning for Deepfake Detection}을 \"Divide-and-Conquer\" 전략 아래에서 제안한다.    \"Divide\" 단계에서는 Geometric View Purification을 사용하여 원칙적인 geometric projection을 통해 얽힌 representation space를 분해한다. 이 과정은 artifact에 민감한 representation 내의 semantic interference를 억제하며, 독립적인 semantic view와 artifact view의 기반을 형성한다.    \"Conquer\" 단계에서는 Uncertainty-Aware Evidential Learning을 활용하여 이들 상이한 view를 통합한다. semantic cue와 artifact cue 사이의 \"epistemic conflict\"를 명시적으로 모델링함으로써, 이 메커니즘은 경직된 결정론적 판단을 강요하는 대신 보정된 uncertainty estimate를 제공한다.   여러 benchmark에 걸친 광범위한 실험은 우리의 방법이 일반화 성능에서 기존 접근법을 일관되게 능가하면서, 신뢰할 수 있는 deepfake detection을 위한 믿을 만한 uncertainty estimation을 제공함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"64604","en":"Foresee-to-Ground: From Predictive Temporal Perception to Evidence-Driven Reasoning for Video Temporal Grounding","ko":"Foresee-to-Ground: Video Temporal Grounding을 위한 예측적 시간 지각에서 증거 기반 추론으로","authors":"Zelin Zheng, Xinyan Liu, Ruixin Li, Antoni B. Chan, Guorong Li, Qingming Huang, Laiyun Qing","pos":"#1006","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Lm3Js8viIP","abs":"<p>Current Video-LLM approaches for Video Temporal Grounding (VTG) typically rely on direct timestamp generation from an unstructured visual-token stream, often resulting in brittle numerics and inconsistent boundaries. To address this, we propose Foresee-to-Ground (F2G), a framework that enforces a verifiable Identify-then-Measure routine. F2G couples predictive temporal perception with evidence-driven reasoning: it learns boundary-sensitive temporal representations to constructs a video-wide evidence pool of candidate event segments, and then augments the LLM input with citable evidence units and enforces identifying the moment by citing the evidence before measuring final metric boundaries under the cited hypothesis. This design decouples event identification from precise measurement, effectively stabilizing the reasoning process. Extensive experiments demonstrate that F2G consistently improves grounding accuracy across diverse benchmarks, transfers robustly across different Video-LLM backbones, and preserves general video understanding capabilities.</p>","absKo":"<p>Video Temporal Grounding (VTG)을 위한 현재 Video-LLM 접근법은 일반적으로 구조화되지 않은 visual-token stream에서 직접 timestamp를 생성하는 데 의존하며, 이로 인해 수치가 취약하고 경계가 일관되지 않는 경우가 많다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 검증 가능한 Identify-then-Measure 절차를 강제하는 프레임워크인 Foresee-to-Ground (F2G)를 제안한다. F2G는 예측적 temporal perception과 evidence-driven reasoning을 결합한다. 구체적으로, 경계에 민감한 temporal representation을 학습하여 후보 event segment로 이루어진 video-wide evidence pool을 구성한 뒤, LLM 입력을 인용 가능한 evidence unit으로 확장하고, 인용된 가설 아래에서 최종 metric boundary를 측정하기 전에 evidence를 인용해 moment를 식별하도록 강제한다. 이러한 설계는 event identification과 정밀한 measurement를 분리하여 reasoning 과정을 효과적으로 안정화한다. 대규모 실험은 F2G가 다양한 benchmark 전반에서 grounding 정확도를 일관되게 향상시키고, 서로 다른 Video-LLM backbone으로 강건하게 transfer되며, 일반적인 video understanding 능력을 보존함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"64173","en":"From Perception to Planning: Evolving Ego-Centric Task-Oriented Spatiotemporal Reasoning via Curriculum Learning","ko":"인식에서 계획으로: 커리큘럼 학습을 통한 자기 중심 과제 지향 시공간 추론의 진화","authors":"Xiaoda Yang, Yuxiang Liu, Shenzhou Gao, Can Wang, Jingyang Xue, Lixin Yang, Yao Mu, Tao Jin, Shuicheng YAN, Zhimeng Zhang, Zhou Zhao","pos":"#1011","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=QHKJhiz88q","abs":"<p>Modern vision-language models achieve strong performance in static perception, but remain limited in the complex spatiotemporal reasoning required for embodied, egocentric tasks. A major source of failure is their reliance on temporal priors learned from passive video data, which often leads to spatiotemporal hallucinations and poor generalization in dynamic environments. To address this, we present EgoTSR, a curriculum-based framework for learning task-oriented spatiotemporal reasoning. EgoTSR is built on the premise that embodied reasoning should evolve from explicit spatial understanding to internalized task-state assessment and finally to long-horizon planning. To support this paradigm, we construct EgoTSR-Data, a large-scale dataset comprising 46 million samples organized into three stages: Chain-of-Thought supervision for explicit reasoning, weakly supervised tagging for internalizing reasoning, and long-horizon sequences composed of orthogonal atomic subtasks. We further introduce a Reasoning-Enhanced Task Decomposition mechanism that explicitly models causal dependencies between actions and objects, enabling controllable planning from high-level task descriptions. To rigorously validate our approach, we establish a Dual-Level Evaluation Framework that covers both atomic spatial perception and logical planning. Extensive experiments demonstrate that EgoTSR effectively eliminates chronological biases, achieving 92.4% accuracy on long-horizon logical reasoning tasks while maintaining 88.2% fine-grained perceptual precision, significantly outperforming existing open-source and closed-source state-of-the-art models.</p>","absKo":"<p>현대의 vision-language model은 정적 지각에서는 강한 성능을 보이지만, embodied하고 egocentric한 과제에서 요구되는 복잡한 spatiotemporal reasoning에는 여전히 한계가 있다. 주요 실패 원인은 passive video data로부터 학습한 temporal prior에 의존하는 데 있으며, 이는 종종 spatiotemporal hallucination과 동적 환경에서의 낮은 일반화로 이어진다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 task-oriented spatiotemporal reasoning을 학습하기 위한 curriculum-based framework EgoTSR을 제시한다. EgoTSR은 embodied reasoning이 명시적 공간 이해에서 내부화된 task-state 평가로, 그리고 궁극적으로 long-horizon planning으로 진화해야 한다는 전제 위에 구축된다. 이 패러다임을 지원하기 위해 우리는 EgoTSR-Data를 구축했다. 이는 명시적 reasoning을 위한 Chain-of-Thought supervision, reasoning internalization을 위한 weakly supervised tagging, 그리고 orthogonal atomic subtask로 구성된 long-horizon sequence라는 세 단계로 조직된 4,600만 개 샘플 규모의 대규모 데이터셋이다. 또한 우리는 행동과 객체 사이의 causal dependency를 명시적으로 모델링하는 Reasoning-Enhanced Task Decomposition 메커니즘을 도입하여, 고수준 task description으로부터 controllable planning을 가능하게 한다. 우리의 접근을 엄격히 검증하기 위해, atomic spatial perception과 logical planning을 모두 포괄하는 Dual-Level Evaluation Framework를 구축했다. 광범위한 실험은 EgoTSR이 chronogical bias를 효과적으로 제거하며, long-horizon logical reasoning task에서 92.4% 정확도를 달성하는 동시에 88.2%의 fine-grained perceptual precision을 유지해, 기존 open-source 및 closed-source state-of-the-art model을 크게 능가함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"61817","en":"Hermes: An Evidence-Driven Agentic Framework for Trustworthy and Explainable AI-Generated Video Detection","ko":"Hermes: 신뢰 가능하고 설명 가능한 AI 생성 비디오 검출을 위한 증거 기반 Agentic Framework","authors":"Shuaibo Li, Pengfei HAO, Hongtao Wu, Jianfeng Dong, Ping Li, Xiaohong Liu, Lei Zhu","pos":"#1012","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=mgtSv2NUik","abs":"<p>Recent advances in generative video models have blurred the boundary between real and synthetic content, raising urgent concerns about digital authenticity. Multimodal large language models (MLLMs) are appealing for AI-generated video (AIGV) forensics due to their broad perceptual and reasoning capabilities; however, existing MLLM-based detectors still suffer from hallucination and unstable reasoning, yielding high false-alarm rates and generic, non-verifiable explanations. To address these issues, we propose Hermes, an evidence-driven agentic framework for trustworthy and explainable AIGV detection. Hermes is realized by three key capabilities: (1) Adaptive Instance-Conditioned Detection Strategy Planning, (2) Evidence-Centric Reasoning and Verification, and (3) Graph-Grounded Evidence Deliberation. Concretely, Hermes employs an instance-conditioned RAG mechanism to analyze each video and retrieve authenticity-verification knowledge for composing a tailored detection strategy. It then performs evidence-centric reasoning by constructing a verifiable Evidence Reasoning Graph (ERG) that maintains focus on authenticity verification and avoids attention drift or superficial reasoning. Finally, a multi-agent deliberation process audits and refines the ERG to reconcile conflicting evidence and enhance reliability. Supported by these capabilities and a rich library of internal and external forensic tools, Hermes achieves structured, verifiable, and interpretable decision-making. Extensive experiments show that Hermes delivers state-of-the-art performance while producing higher-quality, auditable explanations.</p>","absKo":"<p>생성형 video model의 최근 발전은 실제 콘텐츠와 합성 콘텐츠의 경계를 흐리게 만들며, digital authenticity에 대한 시급한 우려를 낳고 있다. Multimodal large language model(MLLM)은 폭넓은 지각 및 추론 능력 때문에 AI-generated video(AIGV) forensic에 매력적이지만, 기존 MLLM 기반 detector는 여전히 hallucination과 불안정한 추론으로 인해 높은 false-alarm rate와 일반적이고 검증 불가능한 설명을 초래한다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해 우리는 신뢰할 수 있고 설명 가능한 AIGV detection을 위한 evidence-driven agentic framework인 Hermes를 제안한다. Hermes는 다음의 세 가지 핵심 능력으로 구현된다: (1) Adaptive Instance-Conditioned Detection Strategy Planning, (2) Evidence-Centric Reasoning and Verification, (3) Graph-Grounded Evidence Deliberation. 구체적으로 Hermes는 instance-conditioned RAG mechanism을 사용해 각 video를 분석하고 authenticity-verification knowledge를 검색하여 맞춤형 detection strategy를 구성한다. 그다음 진위 검증에 초점을 유지하고 attention drift나 피상적 추론을 피하는 검증 가능한 Evidence Reasoning Graph(ERG)를 구성함으로써 evidence-centric reasoning을 수행한다. 마지막으로 multi-agent deliberation process가 ERG를 감사하고 정제하여 상충하는 evidence를 조정하고 신뢰성을 향상시킨다. 이러한 능력과 풍부한 내부 및 외부 forensic tool library를 바탕으로 Hermes는 구조화되고 검증 가능하며 해석 가능한 의사결정을 달성한다. 광범위한 실험은 Hermes가 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성하는 동시에 더 고품질이고 감사 가능한 설명을 생성함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"66040","en":"IVQA-LD: Inclusive Multimodal Understanding for Population with Limb-Deficiency","ko":"IVQA-LD: 사지 결손 인구를 위한 포용적 멀티모달 이해","authors":"Yan Ke, Xin Shen, Jiaying Ying, Xin Li, Xin Yu","pos":"#1013","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=7cZztVrgR0","abs":"<p>People with limb differences often face significant challenges in accessing inclusive AI services, largely due to the lack of structured, high-quality resources centered on disability contexts.  In this work, we introduce a limb-deficiency aware body-centric learning and evaluation paradigm that involves (i) a large-scale limb-aware vision–language dataset and evaluation benchmark for multimodal reasoning, and (ii) a model adaptation strategy for Vision-Language Models (VLM) in limb-difference contexts. Specifically, we first collect limb-difference data covering all eight limb-deficiency types across diverse real-world scenarios. The data are systematically organized into 96 limb-affected human action categories and 68 medical-functional classes defined by the World Health Organization (WHO). Then, we curate an expert-annotated vision–language dataset for limb-aware multimodal understanding, named Inclusive VQA for Limb Deficiency (<strong>IVQA-LD</strong>). IVQA-LD comprises 80K VQA pairs spanning eight core tasks including visual grounding, quantitative reasoning, functional semantic classification, and instructional text generation.  We benchmark state-of-the-art VLMs on IVQA-LD and find that they consistently struggle across all tasks, exposing substantial deficiencies in limb-aware perception and reasoning. To address this, we further propose a Body-centric Structure-aware Initialization (BSI) strategy that aligns model representations with limb-specific semantics. With BSI, VLMs fine-tuned on IVQA-LD achieve significant performance improvements across all the tasks. We will publicly release the dataset to support future research.</p>"},{"id":"60949","en":"InfoGeo: Information-Theoretic Object-Centric Learning for Cross-View Generalizable UAV Geo-Localization","ko":"InfoGeo: Cross-View Generalizable UAV Geo-Localization을 위한 Information-Theoretic Object-Centric Learning","authors":"Hongyang ZHANG, Maonan Wang, Ziyao Wang, Hongrui Yin, Simon Pun","pos":"#1014","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=v6xrfEjNQv","abs":"<p>Cross-view geo-localization (CVGL) is fundamental for precise navigation in GPS-denied environments, aiming to match ground or UAV imagery with satellite views. While existing approaches rely on global feature alignment, they often suffer from substantial domain shifts induced by varying regional textures and weather conditions. This issue becomes even more pronounced in UAV-based scenarios where the broader perspective provided by UAVs inevitably introduces dense and fine-grained objects, creating significant visual clutter. To address this, we draw inspiration from Object-Centric Learning (OCL) and propose InfoGeo, an information-theoretic framework designed to enhance robustness and generalization. InfoGeo reformulates the optimization as an information bottleneck process with two core objectives: (i) maximizing view-invariant information by aligning the object-centric structural relations across views, and (ii) minimizing view-specific noisy signals through cross-view knowledge constraints. Extensive evaluations across diverse benchmarks and challenging scenarios demonstrate that InfoGeo significantly outperforms state-of-the-art methods.</p>","absKo":"<p>Cross-view geo-localization(CVGL)은 GPS가 없는 환경에서 정밀 내비게이션의 핵심으로, 지상 또는 UAV 이미지를 위성 영상과 매칭하는 것을 목표로 한다. 기존 접근법은 전역 특징 정렬에 의존하지만, 지역별 텍스처와 기상 조건의 변화로 인해 유발되는 상당한 domain shift에 자주 취약하다. 이 문제는 UAV가 제공하는 더 넓은 시야가 필연적으로 밀집하고 세분화된 객체들을 포함하게 되어, 큰 시각적 혼잡을 만들어내는 UAV 기반 시나리오에서 더욱 두드러진다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 Object-Centric Learning(OCL)에서 영감을 받아 강건성과 일반화 성능을 향상시키도록 설계된 information-theoretic framework인 InfoGeo를 제안한다. InfoGeo는 최적화를 두 가지 핵심 목표를 갖는 information bottleneck 과정으로 재정식화한다: (i) 뷰 간 object-centric 구조 관계를 정렬하여 view-invariant information을 최대화하고, (ii) cross-view knowledge constraints를 통해 view-specific noisy signals를 최소화하는 것이다. 다양한 benchmark와 어려운 시나리오 전반에 대한 광범위한 평가 결과, InfoGeo가 state-of-the-art methods를 크게 능가함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"63344","en":"Artemis: Structured Visual Reasoning for Perception Policy Learning","ko":"Artemis: 지각 정책 학습을 위한 구조화된 시각적 추론","authors":"Wei Tang, Yanpeng Sun, Shan Zhang, Weihao Bo, Xiaofan Li, Piotr Koniusz, Wei Li, Na Zhao, Zechao Li","pos":"#1106","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=XtIRCAEYoJ","abs":"<p>Recent reinforcement-learning frameworks for visual perception policy usually incorporate intermediate reasoning chains expressed in natural language. Empirical observations indicate that such purely linguistic intermediate reasoning often reduces performance on perception tasks. We argue that the core issue lies not in reasoning per se but in the form of reasoning:  while these chains perform semantic reasoning in an unstructured linguistic space, visual perception requires reasoning in a spatial and object-centric space. In response, we introduce Artemis, a perception-policy learning method that performs structured visual reasoning, where each intermediate step is represented as a (label, bounding-box) pair capturing a verifiable visual state. This design enables explicit tracking of intermediate states, direct supervision for proposal quality, and avoids ambiguity introduced by language-based reasoning. Building upon verifiable and spatially grounded reasoning chains, Artemis provides a unified architecture for diverse perceptual tasks, without requiring the task-specific designs relied upon by prior perceptual policy models. Trained using grounding and detection sampeles in natural image domains, Artemis generalizes to counting and geometric perception tasks. At its core, a spatially grounded, object-centric chain rule provides a principled foundation for scalable and general perceptual policies.</p>","absKo":"<p>visual perception policy를 위한 최근 reinforcement-learning framework는 대개 natural language로 표현된 중간 reasoning chain을 포함한다. 경험적 관찰에 따르면 이러한 순수한 언어 기반 중간 reasoning은 perception task 성능을 오히려 저하시킨다. 우리는 핵심 문제가 reasoning 자체가 아니라 reasoning의 형식에 있다고 주장한다. 이러한 chain이 구조화되지 않은 언어 공간에서 semantic reasoning을 수행하는 반면, visual perception은 spatial하고 object-centric한 공간에서의 reasoning을 필요로 하기 때문이다. 이에 대응하여 우리는 Artemis를 제안하는데, 이는 각 중간 단계를 검증 가능한 visual state를 담은 (label, bounding-box) 쌍으로 표현하는 structured visual reasoning을 수행하는 perception-policy learning 방법이다. 이 설계는 중간 상태의 명시적 추적, proposal quality에 대한 직접 감독, 그리고 language-based reasoning이 야기하는 모호성의 회피를 가능하게 한다. 검증 가능하고 spatially grounded된 reasoning chain 위에 구축된 Artemis는 이전 perceptual policy model이 의존하던 task-specific design 없이도 다양한 perceptual task를 위한 통합된 architecture를 제공한다. natural image domain의 grounding 및 detection sample로 학습된 Artemis는 counting과 geometric perception task로 일반화된다. 그 핵심에는 spatially grounded하고 object-centric한 chain rule이 scalable하고 일반적인 perceptual policy를 위한 원리적인 기반을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"60832","en":"AURA: Visually Interpretable Affective Understanding via Robust Archetypes","ko":"AURA: Robust Archetype을 통한 시각적으로 해석 가능한 감정 이해","authors":"Guanyu Hu, Dimitrios Kollias, Xinyu Yang","pos":"#1107","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=wExPmEZyi3","abs":"<p>Interpretable methods such as Vision–Language Models (VLMs) have advanced affect analysis by aligning images with textual descriptions. However, relying on text as an intermediate proxy faces critical limitations: linguistic templates are inherently discrete, making them fundamentally incompatible with continuous Valence–Arousal (VA) regression, while also acting as a bottleneck for fine-grained visual nuances. Cognitive psychology suggests that human affective perception is not mediated by linguistic translation, but is grounded in direct perceptual resemblance to internalized Visual Archetypes. Motivated by this, we propose AURA, a archetype framework that replaces brittle linguistic proxy with a self-organizing archetype manifold. By adaptively allocating representational density based on data complexity, AURA enables precise continuous regression and reshapes affective taxonomies, decomposing coarse labels into interpretable, geometrically coherent visual primitives. This paradigm offers a transparent, perceptually grounded decision trail, achieving state-of-the-art performance across discrete and continuous tasks.</p>","absKo":"<p>Vision–Language Models(VLMs)와 같은 해석 가능한 방법은 이미지를 textual description과 정렬함으로써 affect analysis를 발전시켜 왔다. 그러나 text를 중간 proxy로 사용하는 방식은 중대한 한계를 지닌다. linguistic template는 본질적으로 discrete이므로 continuous Valence–Arousal(VA) regression과 근본적으로 양립하지 못하며, 동시에 세밀한 visual nuance를 포착하는 데 병목으로 작용한다. Cognitive psychology는 인간의 affective perception이 linguistic translation을 매개로 하지 않으며, 내재화된 Visual Archetype에 대한 직접적인 perceptual resemblance에 기반한다고 제시한다. 이러한 점에서 영감을 받아, 우리는 취약한 linguistic proxy를 self-organizing archetype manifold로 대체하는 archetype framework인 AURA를 제안한다. 데이터 복잡도에 따라 representational density를 적응적으로 할당함으로써, AURA는 정밀한 continuous regression을 가능하게 하고 affective taxonomy를 재구성하여, 거친 라벨을 해석 가능하고 기하학적으로 일관된 visual primitive으로 분해한다. 이 패러다임은 투명하고 지각적으로 grounded된 decision trail을 제공하며, discrete task와 continuous task 전반에서 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"61221","en":"Don't Overthink with Pixels: Efficient Reasoning for Segmentation","ko":"Pixel로 과하게 생각하지 않기: Segmentation을 위한 효율적 추론","authors":"Song Wang, Gongfan Fang, Lingdong Kong, Xiangtai Li, Jianyun Xu, Sheng Yang, Qiang Li, Jianke Zhu, Xinchao Wang","pos":"#1110","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=sXRZoMhNFo","abs":"<p>Existing reasoning segmentation approaches typically fine-tune multimodal large language models (MLLMs) using image-text pairs and corresponding mask labels. While recent efforts leverage reinforcement fine-tuning to further enhance reasoning ability, they often suffer from overthinking and produce uniformly verbose reasoning chains irrespective of task complexity. To address this problem, we propose PixelThink, a simple yet effective scheme that integrates externally estimated task difficulty and internally measured model uncertainty to regulate reasoning generation within a reinforcement learning paradigm.  The model learns to compress reasoning length in accordance with scene complexity and predictive confidence. To support comprehensive evaluation, we introduce ReasonSeg-Diff, an extended benchmark with annotated reasoning references and difficulty scores, along with a suite of metrics designed to assess segmentation accuracy, reasoning quality, and efficiency jointly. Experimental results demonstrate that the proposed approach not only improves segmentation performance  but also significantly reduces inference latency by 30.4%, cutting token usage by 48.2%. The code and model will be publicly available.</p>","absKo":"<p>기존의 reasoning segmentation 접근은 일반적으로 image-text pair와 해당 mask label을 사용해 multimodal large language models (MLLMs)를 fine-tune한다. 최근에는 reinforcement fine-tuning을 활용해 reasoning 능력을 더 향상시키려는 시도도 있었지만, 이들은 과도한 thinking에 시달리며 task 복잡도와 무관하게 일률적으로 장황한 reasoning chain을 생성하는 경우가 많다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 외부에서 추정한 task difficulty와 내부에서 측정한 model uncertainty를 통합하여 reinforcement learning paradigm 안에서 reasoning generation을 조절하는 간단하지만 효과적인 scheme인 PixelThink를 제안한다. 이 model은 scene complexity와 predictive confidence에 맞추어 reasoning 길이를 압축하는 법을 학습한다. 포괄적인 평가를 지원하기 위해, 우리는 주석이 달린 reasoning reference와 difficulty score를 포함하는 확장 benchmark인 ReasonSeg-Diff와 함께, segmentation 정확도, reasoning quality, 효율성을 함께 평가하도록 설계된 metric 세트를 도입한다. 실험 결과는 제안한 접근이 segmentation 성능을 향상시킬 뿐만 아니라 inference latency를 30.4% 줄이고 token 사용량을 48.2% 절감함을 보여준다. 코드와 model은 공개될 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"64307","en":"Don't Forget Why You Started: Tackling Dual Forgetting in Vision-Language Continual Learning","ko":"왜 시작했는지 잊지 마라: Vision-Language 지속 학습에서 이중 망각 대응","authors":"Borui Kang, Jinrui Gu, Tao Feng, Qi Fan, Yinghuan Shi, Lei Wang, Wenbin Li, Yang Gao","pos":"#1111","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=OtuuZ68quP","abs":"<p>Continual learning of Vision-Language Model (VLM) aspires to empower foundation models with new expertise without compromising their universal zero-shot capabilities.  However, this pursuit faces a critical ''dual-forgetting'' challenge: the catastrophic forgetting of newly acquired classes (Incremental Knowledge Forgetting, IKF) and the insidious erosion of foundational zero-shot capabilities (Pre-trained Knowledge Forgetting, PKF).  Existing evaluations often ignore PKF or assess it via confounded protocols where positive transfer on semantically similar domains creates an illusion of retention, masking severe foundational degradation.  To address this, we propose the Dual-Forgetting-Aware Class-Incremental Learning (DFA-CIL) framework and the Similarity-Calibrated Retention (SCR) metric.  Unlike standard averaging, SCR utilizes the frozen pre-trained feature space to inversely weight performance based on semantic similarity, effectively mitigating the confounding gains to stress-test foundational stability. Building on this, we propose DFA-MoE, a functionally heterogeneous Parameter-Efficient Fine-Tuning (PEFT) method.  DFA-MoE architecturally decouples optimization objectives by assigning a momentum-enhanced contrastive expert for feature alignment, and separate plasticity experts that combine classification with auxiliary contrastive learning to adapt to new tasks while retaining historical knowledge. Extensive experiments demonstrate that our framework uncovers the hidden fragility of existing methods and achieves a state-of-the-art balance in preserving both incremental and pre-trained knowledge.</p>","absKo":"<p>Vision-Language Model (VLM)의 continual learning은 foundation model에 새로운 전문성을 부여하면서도 범용 zero-shot capability를 유지하는 것을 목표로 한다. 그러나 이 목표는 치명적인 ''dual-forgetting'' 문제에 직면한다: 새로 획득한 class의 catastrophic forgetting(Incremental Knowledge Forgetting, IKF)과 foundational zero-shot capability의 은밀한 붕괴(Pre-trained Knowledge Forgetting, PKF)이다. 기존 평가는 PKF를 무시하거나, 의미적으로 유사한 도메인에서의 positive transfer가 retention의 착시를 만들어 심각한 foundational degradation을 가리는 혼동된 프로토콜로 이를 평가하는 경우가 많다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 Dual-Forgetting-Aware Class-Incremental Learning (DFA-CIL) framework와 Similarity-Calibrated Retention (SCR) metric을 제안한다. 표준 averaging과 달리, SCR은 frozen pre-trained feature space를 활용하여 semantic similarity에 따라 성능을 역가중함으로써, 혼동된 이득을 효과적으로 완화하고 foundational stability를 엄격하게 검증한다. 이를 바탕으로 우리는 기능적으로 이질적인 Parameter-Efficient Fine-Tuning (PEFT) 방법인 DFA-MoE를 제안한다. DFA-MoE는 optimization objective를 구조적으로 분리하여, feature alignment를 위한 momentum-enhanced contrastive expert와, classification과 auxiliary contrastive learning을 결합한 별도의 plasticity expert를 할당함으로써, 역사적 지식을 유지하면서 새 task에 적응하도록 한다. 광범위한 실험은 우리의 framework가 기존 방법의 숨겨진 취약성을 드러내며, incremental knowledge와 pre-trained knowledge를 모두 보존하는 데 있어 state-of-the-art한 균형을 달성함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"60822","en":"Referring Multiple Regions with Large Multimodal Models via Contextual Latent Steering","ko":"Contextual Latent Steering을 통한 Large Multimodal Model의 다중 영역 지칭","authors":"Yun Xing, Hanyuan Liu, Jiahao Nie, Shijian Lu","pos":"#2712","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=wLE7pnypx2","abs":"<p>Large Multimodal Models (LMMs) have recently demonstrated their proficiency in holistic visual comprehension. However, most of them struggle to tackle region-level perception guided by visual prompts, especially for cases where multiple regions are referred simultaneously, or scenarios where global contexts are necessary for precise visual referring. We introduce Contextual Latent Steering (CSteer), a training-free approach for guiding general LMMs to refer multiple regions contextually, without expensive fine-tuning or architectural modifications. CSteer starts with pre-computing contextual vectors that implicitly represent visual referring behaviors, such as differentiation among regions and attention to global contexts, followed by representation editing during inference time. Experimental results on multiple datasets indicate that general LMMs with CSteer outperform referring LMMs in most cases, suggesting a promising solution in training-free, and setting new state-of-the-art for this field. Codes will be made publicly available.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large Multimodal Models (LMMs)는 최근 전반적인 visual comprehension 능력을 입증했다. 그러나 대부분의 모델은 visual prompt로 유도되는 region-level perception을 처리하는 데 어려움을 겪으며, 특히 여러 region이 동시에 언급되거나 정확한 visual referring을 위해 global context가 필요한 경우에 특히 그렇다. 우리는 expensive fine-tuning이나 architectural modification 없이, 일반적인 LMM이 context를 반영해 여러 region을 refer하도록 유도하는 training-free 접근법인 Contextual Latent Steering (CSteer)를 소개한다. CSteer는 먼저 region 간 구분과 global context에 대한 주의 같은 visual referring behavior를 암묵적으로 나타내는 contextual vector를 사전 계산한 뒤, inference time에 representation editing을 수행한다. 여러 dataset에 대한 실험 결과는 CSteer를 적용한 일반 LMM이 대부분의 경우 referring LMM보다 우수함을 보여 주며, training-free setting에서 유망한 해법임을 시사하고 이 분야의 새로운 state-of-the-art를 설정한다. 코드는 공개될 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"61103","en":"Attend to Anything: Foundation Model for Unified Human Attention Modeling","ko":"Attend to Anything: 통합 인간 주의 모델링을 위한 Foundation Model","authors":"Wenzhuo Zhao, Ronghao Xian, Keren Fu, Qijun Zhao","pos":"#2808","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=tfk5Zpn0AR","abs":"Existing human attention modeling methods persist as highly fragmented across modalities, scenes, and task formulations. Consequently, even with increasing model capacity and data scale, current models predominantly remain scene-dependent and task-specific, failing to practically generalize in real-world applications.   To address the fundamental limitations, we present the Attend to Anything Model (AAM), a multi-modal foundation model that unifies attention modeling across various image, video, and audio-visual tasks and scenes. AAM reformulates attention as an asymmetric entailment relationship organized in a general-to-specific hierarchy, implemented through language prompts with hierarchical embeddings in hyperbolic space. Furthermore, to unify static image and dynamic video attention, we adopt a fluid-dynamics perspective, formulating video-frame attention as a diffusive temporal evolution governed by the Fokker--Planck equation.   Extensive experiments on 16 benchmarks demonstrate that AAM consistently outperforms state-of-the-art methods by an average of 6\\% across various scenarios, while achieving approximately a 4$\\times$ speedup in video inference.   Overall, these results demonstrate that AAM provides a principled foundation for future research on attention and saliency-related tasks.","absKo":"기존 human attention modeling 방법은 modality, scene, task formulation 전반에 걸쳐 매우 파편화되어 있다. 그 결과, 모델 용량과 데이터 규모가 증가했음에도 불구하고, 현재 모델들은 주로 scene-dependent 및 task-specific에 머물러 있으며, 실제 응용에서의 범용적 일반화에 실패하고 있다. 이러한 근본적 한계를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 Attend to Anything Model (AAM)을 제안한다. AAM은 다양한 image, video, audio-visual task와 scene 전반에서 attention modeling을 통합하는 multi-modal foundation model이다. AAM은 attention을 general-to-specific hierarchy로 구성된 asymmetric entailment relationship으로 재정식화하며, hyperbolic space의 hierarchical embedding을 갖는 language prompt를 통해 이를 구현한다. 또한 static image와 dynamic video attention을 통합하기 위해, fluid-dynamics 관점을 채택하여 video-frame attention을 Fokker--Planck equation이 지배하는 diffusive temporal evolution으로 정식화한다. 16개 benchmark에 대한 광범위한 실험은 AAM이 다양한 시나리오에서 state-of-the-art method를 평균 6\\% 향상으로 일관되게 능가하며, video inference에서는 약 4$\\times$의 속도 향상을 달성함을 보여준다. 전반적으로 이러한 결과는 AAM이 attention 및 saliency 관련 task의 미래 연구를 위한 원리 기반의 토대를 제공함을 입증한다."},{"id":"64294","en":"Less is More: Neuroscience-Motivated Probing for Efficient Concept Circuits Tracing","ko":"적을수록 좋다: 효율적 개념 회로 추적을 위한 신경과학 기반 프로빙","authors":"Tang Li, Yanlin Chen, Mengmeng Ma, Xi Peng","pos":"#3312","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=P2dl32LtuQ","abs":"<p>Despite the high accuracy, Vision Transformer (ViT) predictions can be driven by spurious cues. Interpreting their inner workings is therefore essential for safe deployment. Sparse autoencoders (SAEs) shed light on decomposing language-model representations into concepts. However, adapting SAE-based interpretation to ViTs remains challenging due to limited control over concept coverage and subjective, non-scalable feature interpretation. To fill the gaps, motivated by stimulus-efficient probing in systems neuroscience, we propose ViSAE, a compact diagnostic toolbox for interpreting the internal mechanisms of ViTs. Specifically, we introduce a probing suite with 64K images and a 16K visually grounded concept vocabulary, improving concept coverage efficiency by 20× over ImageNet and interpretation accuracy by 28.7% over existing concept sets. We further develop an algorithm that automatically interprets SAE features at scale and causally traces cross-layer interactions to recover ViT inner workings using concept circuits. Our method supports auditing spurious correlations and failure modes, and boosts worst-group accuracy on WaterBirds by 48.2% through concept steering.</p>","absKo":"<p>높은 정확도에도 불구하고, Vision Transformer (ViT)의 예측은 spurious cue에 의해 좌우될 수 있습니다. 따라서 안전한 배치를 위해서는 내부 작동을 해석하는 것이 필수적입니다. Sparse autoencoders (SAEs)는 language model representation을 개념으로 분해하는 데 도움을 줍니다. 그러나 SAE 기반 해석을 ViT에 적용하는 것은 concept coverage에 대한 제한된 제어와 주관적이며 확장성이 낮은 feature interpretation 때문에 여전히 어렵습니다. 이러한 공백을 메우기 위해, systems neuroscience의 stimulus-efficient probing에서 영감을 받아 우리는 ViT의 내부 메커니즘을 해석하기 위한 컴팩트한 진단 toolbox인 ViSAE를 제안합니다. 구체적으로, 우리는 64K images와 16K개의 visually grounded concept vocabulary를 갖춘 probing suite를 도입하여, ImageNet 대비 concept coverage efficiency를 20배, 기존 concept set 대비 interpretation accuracy를 28.7% 향상시킵니다. 또한 SAE feature를 대규모로 자동 해석하고 concept circuit을 사용해 cross-layer interaction을 인과적으로 추적하여 ViT의 내부 작동을 복원하는 알고리즘을 개발합니다. 우리의 방법은 spurious correlation과 failure mode를 감사(audit)하는 데 도움이 되며, concept steering을 통해 WaterBirds에서 worst-group accuracy를 48.2% 향상시킵니다.</p>"},{"id":"62500","en":"Spectral-Progressive Thought Flow for Lightweight Multimodal Reasoning","ko":"경량 멀티모달 추론을 위한 Spectral-Progressive Thought Flow","authors":"Yixian Shen, Zhiheng Yang, Qi Bi, Changshuo Wang, JIA-HONG HUANG, Shuai Wang, Prayag Tiwari, George Floros, Anuj Pathania","pos":"#404","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=g2yb3LhW4L","abs":"Multimodal reasoning often relies on long chains of intermediate textual and visual thoughts, where accumulating visual tokens and dense cross-modal attention incur substantial computation and memory overhead. To address this challenge, we propose Spectral-Progressive Thought Flow (*SpecFlow*), a *novel* lightweight multimodal reasoning framework that represents intermediate visual thoughts in a fixed-size discrete cosine space. By exploiting strong energy compaction, *SpecFlow* preserves global layout and relational structure while introducing high-frequency details only when increased spatial precision is required. To align visual state evolution with linguistic intent, classifier-free guidance enables autoregressive textual thoughts to steer flow-based updates of the visual workspace without expanding the context. As a result,*SpecFlow* maintains a bounded visual workspace whose updates depend only on the current visual state and accumulated textual trace, enabling long-horizon inference with stable latency and memory usage independent of reasoning depth. Empirical results show that *SpecFlow* achieves competitive or superior reasoning performance while reducing computation and memory costs by up to *$2.1\\times$*.","absKo":"다중모달 reasoning은 종종 중간 단계의 긴 텍스트 및 시각적 thought chain에 의존하며, 시각 토큰의 누적과 촘촘한 cross-modal attention은 상당한 계산 및 메모리 오버헤드를 유발한다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해 우리는 Spectral-Progressive Thought Flow (*SpecFlow*)를 제안한다. *SpecFlow*는 중간 visual thought를 고정 크기의 discrete cosine space로 표현하는 *novel*한 경량 multimodal reasoning framework이다. 강한 energy compaction을 활용하여 *SpecFlow*는 global layout과 relational structure를 보존하면서, 공간적 정밀도가 더 필요할 때만 고주파 세부 정보를 도입한다. visual state evolution을 linguistic intent와 정렬하기 위해 classifier-free guidance를 사용하여, autoregressive textual thought가 context를 확장하지 않으면서 flow-based update를 visual workspace에 대해 이끌도록 한다. 그 결과 *SpecFlow*는 업데이트가 현재 visual state와 누적된 textual trace에만 의존하는 bounded visual workspace를 유지하며, reasoning depth와 무관하게 안정적인 latency와 memory usage로 long-horizon inference를 가능하게 한다. 실험 결과는 *SpecFlow*가 최대 *$2.1\\times$*까지 계산과 메모리 비용을 줄이면서도 경쟁력 있거나 더 우수한 reasoning 성능을 달성함을 보여준다."},{"id":"64396","en":"SLIP-RS: Structured-Attribute Language-Image Pre-Training for Remote Sensing Object Detection","ko":"SLIP-RS: 원격 탐사 객체 탐지를 위한 구조화 속성 언어-이미지 사전학습","authors":"Chenxu Wang, Yuxuan Li, Yunheng Li, Xiang Li, Jingyuan Xia, Qibin Hou","pos":"#801","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=O2znfxqcIj","abs":"<p>Existing language-image pre-training for remote sensing object detection is constrained by Monolithic Label Learning, which relies on exhaustively enumerating open-set categories via black-box data to acquire fine-grained representations, creating a dependency incompatible with the domain's inherent data scarcity.  To transcend this bottleneck, we propose SLIP-RS, establishing a Structured-Attribute Decoupling Paradigm that maps the open-ended category space into a finite, physically meaningful attribute space, unlocking fine-grained discriminability via explicit structural logic.  This paradigm is realized via two technical pillars:  (1) Structured-Attribute Contrastive Learning, which enforces the learning of decoupled intrinsic visual logic via combinatorial attribute augmentation;  and (2) Conformal Attribute Reliability Engine, which leverages conformal prediction theory to rigorously distill high-fidelity supervision from noisy sources, yielding RS-Attribute-15M, the largest dataset with over 15 million attribute annotations.  Extensive experiments demonstrate that SLIP-RS establishes unprecedented performance in fine-grained detection and cross-domain generalization, validating structured attributes as a vital foundation for scalable remote sensing models.</p>","absKo":"원격탐사 객체 검출을 위한 기존 language-image pre-training은 Monolithic Label Learning의 제약을 받는다. 이는 fine-grained representation을 획득하기 위해 black-box data를 통해 open-set category를 전부 열거하는 방식에 의존하며, 도메인의 본질적인 데이터 희소성과 양립할 수 없는 의존성을 만든다. 이러한 병목을 넘어, 우리는 SLIP-RS를 제안한다. 이는 open-ended category space를 유한하고 물리적으로 의미 있는 attribute space로 매핑하는 Structured-Attribute Decoupling Paradigm을 확립하여, 명시적 구조적 논리를 통해 fine-grained discriminability를 열어준다. 이 패러다임은 두 가지 기술적 축으로 구현된다: (1) combinatorial attribute augmentation을 통해 분리된 intrinsic visual logic의 학습을 강제하는 Structured-Attribute Contrastive Learning, (2) conformal prediction theory를 활용해 noisy source로부터 고신뢰 supervision을 엄밀하게 추출하는 Conformal Attribute Reliability Engine이다. 이를 통해 1,500만 개 이상의 attribute annotation을 포함한 가장 큰 데이터셋인 RS-Attribute-15M을 구축한다. 광범위한 실험은 SLIP-RS가 fine-grained detection과 cross-domain generalization에서 전례 없는 성능을 확립하며, structured attribute가 확장 가능한 remote sensing model의 핵심 기반임을 검증한다.</p>"},{"id":"61569","en":"STORM: Segment, Track, and Object Re-Localization from a Single Image","ko":"STORM: 단일 이미지에서 Segment, Track, Object Re-Localization","authors":"Yu Deng, Teng Cao, Hikaru Shindo, Quentin Delfosse, Jiahong Xue, Kristian Kersting","pos":"#802","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=oqUjAjGQY3","abs":"<p>Accurate 6D pose estimation and tracking are core capabilities for physical AI systems, yet real-world deployment remains brittle and labor-intensive.  Many pipelines rely on CAD models, manual masking, or per-object adaptation, and still fail under occlusion or fast motion without a principled way to recognize failure.  We propose STORM, a unified framework for reference-conditioned 6D tracking with minimal manual input and improved robustness.  STORM introduces two mechanisms: (i) Hierarchical Spatial Fusion Attention (HSFA), which performs latent manifold alignment between reference and query features, guided by vision-language semantic conditioning to resolve instance ambiguities; and (ii) an energy-based failure detector to detect drift and trigger automatic re-initialization, yielding a self-healing tracker. Experiments on LM-O and YCB-Video show that STORM improves annotation-free pose tracking accuracy over strong baselines and recovers reliably from severe occlusions and rapid viewpoint changes with minimal overhead.</p>","absKo":"<p>정확한 6D pose estimation과 tracking은 physical AI 시스템의 핵심 기능이지만, 실제 배포에서는 여전히 취약하고 수작업이 많이 든다. 많은 pipeline이 CAD model, 수동 masking, 또는 object별 adaptation에 의존하며, 그럼에도 occlusion이나 빠른 motion 아래에서는 실패를 원칙적으로 인식하지 못한 채 무너진다. 우리는 최소한의 수동 입력과 향상된 robustness를 갖춘 reference-conditioned 6D tracking을 위한 통합 framework인 STORM을 제안한다. STORM은 두 가지 메커니즘을 도입한다: (i) Hierarchical Spatial Fusion Attention(HSFA)으로, vision-language semantic conditioning의 지도를 받아 reference와 query feature 사이의 latent manifold alignment를 수행하여 instance ambiguity를 해소한다; (ii) drift를 탐지하고 자동 re-initialization을 트리거하는 energy-based failure detector로, self-healing tracker를 구현한다. LM-O와 YCB-Video 실험에서 STORM은 annotation-free pose tracking accuracy를 강력한 baseline보다 향상시키고, 최소한의 overhead로 심한 occlusion과 급격한 viewpoint 변화에서도 안정적으로 복구함을 보였다.</p>"},{"id":"65229","en":"VideoLoom: A Video Large Language Model for Joint Spatial-Temporal Understanding","ko":"VideoLoom: 결합 공간-시간 이해를 위한 Video Large Language Model","authors":"Jiapeng Shi, junke Wang, Zuyao You, Bo He, Zuxuan Wu","pos":"#813","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=FZroB6jcpN","abs":"Recent advancements in Video Large Language Models (Video LLMs) have demonstrated impressive results, yet existing approaches handle either temporal or spatial dimension in isolation, struggling in the analysis of complex events that require spatial-temporal integration. To bridge this gap, we propose VideoLoom, a unified Video LLM for joint spatial-temporal understanding. To facilitate the development of fine-grained spatial and temporal localization capabilities, we curate LoomData-8.7k, a character-centric video dataset with temporally grounded and spatially localized captions. With this, VideoLoom achieves the state-of-the-art performance across a variety of spatial and temporal benchmarks. In addition, we introduce LoomBench, a benchmark consisting of temporal, spatial, and compositional video–question pairs, with a novel metric $J$&amp;$F_{bi-fore}$, enabling a comprehensive evaluation of Video LLMs from diverse aspects. Collectively, these contributions offer a universal and effective suite for joint spatial-temporal video understanding, setting a new standard in multimodal intelligence."},{"id":"61929","en":"VideoVeritas: AI-Generated Video Detection via Perception Pretext Reinforcement Learning","ko":"VideoVeritas: Perception Pretext Reinforcement Learning 기반 AI 생성 비디오 탐지","authors":"Hao Tan, jun lan, Senyuan Shi, Zichang Tan, Zijian Yu, Huijia Zhu, Weiqiang Wang, Jun Wan, Zhen Lei","pos":"#814","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=lbRi2aAWL7","abs":"<p>The growing capability of video generation poses escalating security risks, making reliable detection increasingly essential. In this paper, we introduce <strong>VideoVeritas</strong>, a framework that integrates fine-grained perception and fact-based reasoning. We observe that while current multi-modal large language models (MLLMs) exhibit strong reasoning capacity, their granular perception ability remains limited. To mitigate this, we introduce <em>Joint Preference Alignment</em> and <em>Perception Pretext Reinforcement Learning (PPRL)</em>. Specifically, rather than directly optimizing for detection task, we adopt general spatiotemporal grounding and self-supervised object counting in the RL stage, enhancing detection performance with simple <em>perception pretext tasks</em>. To facilitate robust evaluation, we further introduce <strong>MintVid</strong>, a light yet high-quality dataset containing 3K videos from 9 state-of-the-art generators, along with a real-world collected subset that has factual errors in content. Experimental results demonstrate that existing methods tend to bias towards either <em>superficial</em> reasoning or <em>mechanical</em> analysis, while <strong>VideoVeritas</strong> achieves more balanced performance across diverse benchmarks.</p>","absKo":"<p>video generation의 능력이 커짐에 따라 보안 위험도 함께 커지고 있어, 신뢰할 수 있는 탐지가 점점 더 중요해지고 있다. 본 논문에서는 세밀한 perception과 fact-based reasoning을 통합한 framework <strong>VideoVeritas</strong>를 소개한다. 우리는 현재의 multi-modal large language model (MLLM)이 강한 reasoning capacity를 보이는 반면, 세밀한 perception 능력은 여전히 제한적이라는 점을 관찰했다. 이를 완화하기 위해 <em>Joint Preference Alignment</em>와 <em>Perception Pretext Reinforcement Learning (PPRL)</em>을 도입한다. 구체적으로, detection task를 직접 최적화하는 대신 RL stage에서 일반적인 spatiotemporal grounding과 self-supervised object counting을 채택하여, 단순한 <em>perception pretext task</em>로 detection 성능을 향상시킨다. 강건한 평가를 위해, 우리는 9개의 state-of-the-art generator로부터 생성된 3K videos를 포함하는 가볍지만 고품질인 dataset <strong>MintVid</strong>와, 내용에 사실 오류가 포함된 real-world 수집 subset을 추가로 도입한다. 실험 결과, 기존 방법은 <em>superficial</em> reasoning 또는 <em>mechanical</em> analysis 중 하나에 치우치는 경향이 있는 반면, <strong>VideoVeritas</strong>는 다양한 benchmark 전반에서 더 균형 잡힌 성능을 달성함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"65976","en":"VisionPulse: Dynamic Visual Sparsity for Efficient Multimodal Reasoning","ko":"VisionPulse: 효율적 멀티모달 추론을 위한 동적 시각 희소성","authors":"Hengbo Xu, Shengjie Jin, Yanbiao Ma, Zhiwu Lu","pos":"#815","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=8HeUwrVLIu","abs":"<p>With the rapid advancement of large multimodal models (LMMs), inference-time overhead has become a key bottleneck for real-world deployment.  Existing methods typically prune visual tokens at prefill, assuming the required visual evidence remains static during reasoning.  However, we empirically show that visual evidence is strongly step-dependent: only a sparse subset of visual tokens is critical at each decoding step, and the critical set evolves across reasoning. Furthermore, we identify a coupled bottleneck where redundant visual context can steer the model toward query-irrelevant regions, lengthening the reasoning trace. Guided by these insights, we propose <strong>VisionPulse</strong>, a step-wise visual token pruning framework during reasoning.  VisionPulse computes a lightweight visual attention mass to estimate the step-wise retention budget by exploiting its strong positive correlation with LMMs' effective visual token usage and retain only the most critical tokens under this budget.  By enforcing visual sparsity during reasoning, VisionPulse filters redundant visual context while preserving relevant visual evidence, shortening reasoning traces naturally. Extensive experiments show that VisionPulse only retains 5\\% of visual tokens per step with reasoning traces shortened by 11.2\\%, while keeping accuracy almost unchanged.</p>"},{"id":"62671","en":"Real-Time Visual Attribution Streaming in Thinking Model","ko":"Thinking Model에서의 실시간 Visual Attribution Streaming","authors":"Seil Kang, Woojung Han, Junhyeok Kim, Jinyeong Kim, Youngeun Kim, Seong Jae Hwang","pos":"#902","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=eVr10aZZIw","abs":"<p>We present an amortized framework for real-time visual attribution streaming in multimodal thinking models. When these models generate code from a screenshot or solve math problems from images, their long reasoning traces should be grounded in visual evidence. However, verifying this reliance is challenging: faithful causal methods require costly repeated backward passes or perturbations, while raw attention maps offer instant access, they lack causal validity. To resolve this, we introduce an amortized approach that learns to estimate the causal effects of semantic regions directly from the rich signals encoded in attention features. Across five diverse benchmarks and four thinking models, our approach achieves faithfulness comparable to exhaustive causal methods while enabling visual attribution streaming, where users observe grounding evidence as the model reasons, not after. Our results demonstrate that real-time, faithful attribution in multimodal thinking models is achievable through lightweight learning, not brute-force computation.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 multimodal thinking model에서 실시간 visual attribution streaming을 위한 amortized framework를 제시한다. 이들 model이 screenshot으로부터 code를 생성하거나 이미지로 수학 문제를 풀 때, 긴 reasoning trace는 visual evidence에 근거해야 한다. 그러나 이러한 의존성을 검증하는 것은 어렵다. faithful causal method는 비용이 큰 반복 backward pass나 perturbation을 요구하고, raw attention map은 즉시 접근 가능하지만 causal validity가 부족하다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 attention feature에 인코딩된 풍부한 signal로부터 semantic region의 causal effect를 직접 추정하도록 학습하는 amortized approach를 도입한다. 다섯 개의 다양한 benchmark와 네 개의 thinking model 전반에서, 우리의 접근법은 exhaustive causal method와 동등한 수준의 faithfulness를 달성하면서 visual attribution streaming을 가능하게 한다. 즉, 사용자는 모델이 추론하는 동안, 아니라 끝난 뒤가 아니라 grounding evidence를 관찰할 수 있다. 우리의 결과는 multimodal thinking model에서의 실시간이고 faithful한 attribution이 brute-force computation이 아니라 가벼운 learning으로 달성 가능함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"63267","en":"RSAgent: Learning to Reason and Act via Multi-Turn Tool Invocations for Text-Guided Segmentation","ko":"RSAgent: 텍스트 유도 분할을 위한 다중 턴 도구 호출을 통한 추론 및 행동 학습","authors":"Xingqi He, Yujie Zhang, Shuyong Gao, Wenjie Li, Lingyi Hong, Mingxi Chen, Kaixun Jiang, Jiyuan Fu, Wenqiang Zhang","pos":"#904","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=YYm8Cwn1J3","abs":"<p>Text-guided object segmentation requires both cross-modal reasoning and pixel grounding abilities. Most recent methods treat it as a single forward pass, where the model directly predicts pixel prompts to a segmentation model, which limits verification, refocusing and refinement when initial localization is wrong. To address this limitation, we propose <strong>RSAgent</strong>, an agentic Multimodal Large Language Model (MLLM) which interleaves <strong>reasoning and action</strong> for segmentation via multi-turn tool invocations. RSAgent queries a visual toolbox, observes feedback, and revises its pixel hypothesis using historical observations to re-localize targets and iteratively refine masks. We further build a data pipeline to synthesize multi-turn reasoning segmentation trajectories, and train RSAgent with a two-stage framework: cold-start supervised fine-tuning followed by agentic reinforcement learning with fine-grained, task-specific rewards.  Extensive experiments show that RSAgent achieves a zero-shot performance of 66.5% gIoU on ReasonSeg test, improving over Seg-Zero-7B by 9%, and reaches 81.5% cIoU on RefCOCOg, demonstrating state-of-the-art performance on both in-domain and out-of-domain benchmarks.</p>","absKo":"<p>텍스트 유도 객체 분할은 cross-modal reasoning과 pixel grounding 능력을 모두 요구한다. 최근의 대부분 방법은 이를 단일 forward pass로 취급하여, 모델이 segmentation model에 전달할 pixel prompt를 직접 예측하게 한다. 이는 초기 localizaton이 잘못되었을 때 verification, refocusing, refinement를 제한한다. 이 한계를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 멀티턴 tool invocation을 통해 분할을 위한 <strong>reasoning and action</strong>을 교차적으로 수행하는 agentic Multimodal Large Language Model (MLLM)인 <strong>RSAgent</strong>를 제안한다. RSAgent는 visual toolbox를 질의하고, feedback을 관찰하며, historical observations를 사용해 pixel hypothesis를 수정하여 target을 다시 localize하고 mask를 반복적으로 정제한다. 또한 멀티턴 reasoning segmentation trajectory를 합성하는 데이터 파이프라인을 구축하고, cold-start supervised fine-tuning 이후 fine-grained task-specific reward를 사용하는 agentic reinforcement learning을 적용하는 2-stage framework로 RSAgent를 학습한다. 광범위한 실험 결과, RSAgent는 ReasonSeg test에서 66.5% gIoU의 zero-shot 성능을 달성하여 Seg-Zero-7B보다 9% 향상되었고, RefCOCOg에서 81.5% cIoU에 도달하여 in-domain 및 out-of-domain benchmark 모두에서 state-of-the-art 성능을 입증했다.</p>"},{"id":"66696","en":"PhaseAlign: Complex Phase Alignment for Stable Open-Vocabulary Semantic Segmentation","ko":"PhaseAlign: 안정적인 Open-Vocabulary Semantic Segmentation을 위한 복소 위상 정렬","authors":"Jiankang Wang, Dingding Jia, Zhoushuopeng, Xuan Wang","pos":"#907","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=1Gd7pQr7FQ","abs":"<p>Open-Vocabulary Segmentation(OVS) aims to achieve pixel-level semantic recognition from arbitrary text queries. Existing large-scale visual-linguistic models, such as CLIP, perform well in zero-shot generalization, but their image-level training objectives and real-valued cross-modal alignment mix amplitude and phase information, limiting fine-grained segmentation and often causing blurred boundaries and fragmented structures. Inspired by the ability of electromagnetic wave phase to control interference independently of amplitude, we propose PhaseAlign, an OVS framework based on Complex Phase Alignment (CPA). CPA explicitly decouples the magnitude and phase of visual and textual embeddings in the complex domain, refining effective features for stable cross-modal alignment. To further enhance structural awareness, we introduce spatial-aware cross-modal projection, which models local neighborhood relations via multi-scale spatial contrast normalization, and attention-guided affinity modeling, which leverages pre-trained ViT self-attention to propagate category activations, improving boundary clarity and region integrity. Experiments show that PhaseAlign achieves state-of-the-art performance on multiple OVS benchmarks.</p>"},{"id":"64285","en":"Linguistic Relative Policy Optimization for Video Anomaly Reasoning","ko":"영상 이상 추론을 위한 언어적 상대 정책 최적화","authors":"Jiaxu Leng, Jiankang Zheng, Mengjingcheng Mo, Zhanjie Wu, Haosheng Chen, Ji Gan, Xinbo Gao","pos":"#915","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=P8tBsNibfm","abs":"<p>Video anomaly detection (VAD) with multimodal large language models has shown strong potential, yet most existing methods still depend on large-scale annotations or expert-designed priors, limiting their ability to acquire anomaly knowledge with as little human intervention as possible. To address this, we propose Linguistic Relative Policy Optimization (LRPO), which distills group-relative semantic advantages from multiple reasoning trajectories into a linguistically expressed anomaly experience prior, and adapts the model by injecting this prior into the context to steer its output distribution without any parameter updates. LRPO builds two complementary experience representations: general experience captures transferable anomaly preferences across scenarios, while scenario experience models context-dependent anomaly rules for targeted refinement. To further improve the learned experience, we introduce an anomaly alignment reward that guides trajectory optimization to match human risk preferences and reinforce temporally grounded reasoning. Extensive experiments on XD-Violence, UCF-Crime, and UBNormal demonstrate that LRPO significantly outperforms existing state-of-the-art methods under tuning-free settings.</p>","absKo":"<p>multimodal large language model을 활용한 video anomaly detection (VAD)은 강한 잠재력을 보였지만, 기존 method의 대부분은 여전히 대규모 annotation이나 전문가가 설계한 prior에 의존하여, 가능한 한 적은 human intervention으로 anomaly knowledge를 습득하는 능력을 제한한다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 Linguistic Relative Policy Optimization (LRPO)를 제안한다. LRPO는 여러 reasoning trajectory로부터 group-relative semantic advantage를 증류하여 언어적으로 표현된 anomaly experience prior로 만들고, 이 prior를 context에 주입해 parameter update 없이 output distribution을 유도함으로써 model을 적응시킨다. LRPO는 두 가지 상호 보완적인 experience representation을 구성한다. general experience는 서로 다른 scenario 전반에서 전이 가능한 anomaly 선호를 포착하고, scenario experience는 targeted refinement를 위한 context-dependent anomaly rule을 모델링한다. 학습된 experience를 더 향상시키기 위해, 우리는 trajectory optimization이 human risk preference와 정렬되고 시간적으로 grounded된 reasoning을 강화하도록 유도하는 anomaly alignment reward를 도입한다. XD-Violence, UCF-Crime, UBNormal에 대한 광범위한 실험은 LRPO가 tuning-free 설정에서 기존 state-of-the-art method를 유의미하게 능가함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"66485","en":"SCalDA: Semantics-Calibrated and Diffusion-Enhanced Data Augmentation","ko":"SCalDA: 의미론 보정 및 Diffusion 강화 데이터 증강","authors":"Shibo Lv, Jianmin Jiang","pos":"#900","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=3HPAnV6LdO","abs":"<p>With the rapid development of deep learning, the issue of data scarcity has become increasingly prominent, inspiring emerging interests towards research on data augmentation techniques over recent years. However, our literature survey indicates that existing efforts often suffer from two issues of semantic infidelity, including: (i) visual semantics infidelity, such as visual artifacts, manifold intrusion, and unnatural blending boundaries etc, and (ii) label semantic infidelity, where augmented images do not match the original labels, creating extra label noises. To address these issues, we propose a Semantics Calibrated and Diffusion-Enhanced Augmentation (SCalDA) scheme to achieve accurate semantics calibration across image, label and feature domains. Compared with the existing approaches, our proposed features in precise guidance in label domain, semantics driven synthesis across three domains (image, label and feature), and semantics-aware metric learning. Extensive experiments on multiple datasets demonstrate that SCalDA yields consistent and significant performance improvements for both fine-grained and general classification tasks, validating the effectiveness and broad applicability of the proposed.</p>"},{"id":"63881","en":"NoiseSDF2NoiseSDF: Learning Clean Neural Fields from Noisy Supervision","ko":"NoiseSDF2NoiseSDF: 노이즈가 있는 supervision으로 깨끗한 neural field 학습","authors":"Tengkai Wang, Weihao Li, Ruikai Cui, Shi Qiu, Nick Barnes","pos":"#910","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=SqegQxm1ya","abs":"<p>Reconstructing accurate implicit surface representations from point clouds remains a challenging task, particularly when data is captured using low-quality scanning devices. These point clouds often contain substantial noise, leading to inaccurate surface reconstructions. Inspired by the Noise2Noise paradigm for 2D images, we introduce NoiseSDF2NoiseSDF, a novel method designed to extend this concept to 3D neural fields. Our approach enables learning clean neural SDFs from noisy point clouds through noisy supervision by minimizing the MSE loss between noisy SDF representations, allowing the network to implicitly denoise and refine surface estimations. We evaluate the effectiveness of NoiseSDF2NoiseSDF on benchmarks, including the ShapeNet, ABC, Famous, and Real datasets. Experimental results demonstrate that our framework significantly improves surface reconstruction quality from noisy inputs.</p>","absKo":"<p>Point cloud로부터 정확한 implicit surface representation을 복원하는 일은 여전히 어려운 과제이며, 특히 데이터가 저품질 스캐닝 장치로 수집된 경우 더욱 그렇다. 이러한 point cloud에는 종종 상당한 noise가 포함되어 있어 surface reconstruction이 부정확해진다. 2D image에서의 Noise2Noise paradigm에 영감을 받아, 우리는 이 개념을 3D neural field로 확장하기 위해 설계된 새로운 방법 NoiseSDF2NoiseSDF를 소개한다. 우리의 접근법은 noisy supervision을 통해 noisy point cloud로부터 clean neural SDF를 학습할 수 있게 하며, noisy SDF representation 간의 MSE loss를 최소화함으로써 network가 implicit하게 denoise하고 surface estimation을 refine하도록 한다. 우리는 ShapeNet, ABC, Famous, Real dataset을 포함한 benchmark에서 NoiseSDF2NoiseSDF의 효과를 평가한다. 실험 결과는 우리의 framework가 noisy input으로부터의 surface reconstruction 품질을 크게 향상시킴을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"60731","en":"From Blind Spots to Gains: Diagnostic-Driven Iterative Training for Large Multimodal Models","ko":"Blind Spot에서 성능 향상으로: Large Multimodal Model을 위한 진단 기반 반복 학습","authors":"Hongrui Jia, Chaoya Jiang, Yongrui Heng, Shikun Zhang, Wei Ye","pos":"#1009","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=x7LWdQlwY7","abs":"<p>As Large Multimodal Models (LMMs) scale up and reinforcement learning (RL) methods mature, LMMs have made notable progress in complex reasoning and decision making. Yet training still relies on static data and fixed recipes, making it difficult to diagnose capability blind spots or provide dynamic, targeted reinforcement. Motivated by findings that test driven error exposure and feedback based correction outperform repetitive practice, we propose Diagnostic-driven Progressive Evolution (DPE), a spiral loop where diagnosis steers data generation and reinforcement, and each iteration re-diagnoses the updated model to drive the next round of targeted improvement. DPE has two key components. First, multiple agents annotate and quality control massive unlabeled multimodal data, using tools such as web search and image editing to produce diverse, realistic samples. Second, DPE attributes failures to specific weaknesses, dynamically adjusts the data mixture, and guides agents to generate weakness focused data for targeted reinforcement. Experiments on Qwen3-VL-8B-Instruct and Qwen2.5-VL-7B-Instruct show stable, continual gains across eleven benchmarks, indicating DPE as a scalable paradigm for continual LMM training under open task distributions.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large Multimodal Models (LMMs)가 규모를 키우고 reinforcement learning (RL) 방법이 성숙해지면서, LMMs는 복잡한 추론과 의사결정에서 눈에 띄는 진전을 보여 왔다. 그러나 학습은 여전히 정적인 데이터와 고정된 레시피에 의존하므로, 역량의 사각지대를 진단하거나 동적으로 표적화된 강화 신호를 제공하기가 어렵다. test-driven error exposure와 feedback-based correction이 반복적 연습보다 더 우수하다는 발견에 동기를 얻어, 우리는 Diagnostic-driven Progressive Evolution (DPE)을 제안한다. DPE는 진단이 데이터 생성과 reinforcement를 이끄는 나선형 루프로, 각 반복에서 업데이트된 모델을 다시 진단하여 다음 라운드의 표적 개선을 유도한다. DPE는 두 가지 핵심 구성요소를 가진다. 첫째, 여러 agent가 web search와 image editing 같은 도구를 사용해 대규모 unlabeled multimodal data에 주석을 달고 품질을 관리하여, 다양하고 현실적인 샘플을 생성한다. 둘째, DPE는 실패를 특정 약점에 귀속시키고, 데이터 mixture를 동적으로 조정하며, agent가 약점에 초점을 맞춘 데이터를 생성하도록 유도해 표적 강화 학습을 수행한다. Qwen3-VL-8B-Instruct와 Qwen2.5-VL-7B-Instruct에서의 실험은 11개 benchmark 전반에 걸쳐 안정적이고 지속적인 향상을 보여 주었으며, DPE가 open task distributions 하에서 continual LMM training을 위한 확장 가능한 paradigm임을 시사한다.</p>"},{"id":"61892","en":"Context Forcing: Consistent Autoregressive Video Generation with Long Context","ko":"Context Forcing: 긴 문맥의 일관된 자기회귀 비디오 생성","authors":"Shuo Chen, Cong Wei, Sun Sun, Tiancheng SHEN, Ping Nie, Kai Zou, Ge Zhang, Ming-Hsuan Yang, Wenhu Chen","pos":"#1000","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=lv86f7Qr9V","abs":"Recent approaches to real-time long video generation typically employ streaming tuning strategies, attempting to train a long-context student using a short-context (memoryless) teacher. In these frameworks, the student performs long rollouts but receives supervision from a teacher limited to short 5-second windows. This structural discrepancy creates a critical **student-teacher mismatch**: the teacher's inability to access long-term history prevents it from guiding the student on global temporal dependencies, effectively capping the student's context length. To resolve this, we propose **Context Forcing**, a novel framework that trains a long-context student via a long-context teacher. By ensuring the teacher is aware of the full generation history, we eliminate the supervision mismatch, enabling the robust training of models capable of long-term consistency. To make this computationally feasible for extreme durations (e.g., 2 minute), we introduce a context management system that transforms the linearly growing context into a **Slow-Fast Memory** architecture, significantly reducing visual redundancy. Extensive results demonstrate that our method enables effective context lengths exceeding 20 seconds—$6\\text{--}10\\times$ longer than state-of-the-art methods like LongLive and Infinite-RoPE. By leveraging this extended context, Context Forcing preserves superior consistency across long durations, surpassing state-of-the-art baselines on various long video evaluation metrics.","absKo":"최근 real-time long video generation 접근법은 대체로 streaming tuning 전략을 사용하여, short-context (memoryless) teacher를 이용해 long-context student를 학습시키려 한다. 이러한 프레임워크에서 student는 긴 rollout을 수행하지만 길이 5초의 짧은 window에 국한된 teacher로부터 supervision을 받는다. 이 구조적 불일치는 치명적인 **student-teacher mismatch**를 만든다. 즉, teacher가 장기 history에 접근할 수 없기 때문에 student의 global temporal dependency를 안내하지 못하며, 결과적으로 student의 context length가 사실상 제한된다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 long-context teacher를 통해 long-context student를 학습하는 새로운 프레임워크인 **Context Forcing**을 제안한다. teacher가 전체 generation history를 인지하도록 보장함으로써 supervision mismatch를 제거하고, 장기 일관성을 유지할 수 있는 model의 견고한 학습을 가능하게 한다. 극단적으로 긴 duration(예: 2분)에서도 계산 가능하도록 만들기 위해, 우리는 선형적으로 증가하는 context를 **Slow-Fast Memory** architecture로 변환하는 context management system을 도입하여 visual redundancy를 크게 줄인다. 광범위한 결과는 우리의 방법이 20초를 넘는 효과적인 context length를 가능하게 하며, 이는 LongLive와 Infinite-RoPE 같은 state-of-the-art 방법보다 $6\\text{--}10\\times$ 더 긴 것이다. 확장된 context를 활용함으로써 Context Forcing은 긴 시간에 걸쳐 더 우수한 consistency를 유지하고, 다양한 long video evaluation metric에서 state-of-the-art baseline을 능가한다."},{"id":"65464","en":"FAIL: Flow Matching Adversarial Imitation Learning for Image Generation","ko":"FAIL: 이미지 생성을 위한 Flow Matching 적대적 모방 학습","authors":"Yeyao Ma, Chen Li, Xiaosong Zhang, Han Hu, Weidi Xie","pos":"#1004","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=DQK5CYXCYd","abs":"<p>Post-training of flow matching models—aligning the output distribution with a high-quality target—is mathematically equivalent to imitation learning. While Supervised Fine-Tuning mimics expert demonstrations effectively, it cannot correct policy drift in unseen states. Preference optimization methods address this but require costly preference pairs or reward modeling. We propose Flow Matching Adversarial Imitation Learning (FAIL), which minimizes policy-expert divergence through adversarial training without explicit rewards or pairwise comparisons. We derive two algorithms: FAIL-PD exploits differentiable ODE solvers for low-variance pathwise gradients, while FAIL-PG provides a black-box alternative for discrete or computationally constrained settings. Fine-tuning FLUX with only 13,000 demonstrations from Nano Banana pro, FAIL achieves competitive performance on prompt following and aesthetic benchmarks. Furthermore, the framework generalizes effectively to discrete image and video generation, and functions as a robust regularizer to mitigate reward hacking in reward-based optimization.</p>"},{"id":"63754","en":"FlowSeg: Dynamic Semantic Guidance for LLM-Conditioned Segmentation","ko":"FlowSeg: LLM 조건부 segmentation을 위한 동적 의미 가이던스","authors":"Zekang Zhang, Guangyu Gao, YouyunTang, WU CHENGJING, Chi Harold Liu, Xiaochao Qu, Luoqi Liu, Ting Liu, Jianbo Jiao, Yunchao Wei","pos":"#1005","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=TzzJped56P","abs":"<p>LLM-conditioned segmentation has recently advanced rapidly by coupling large language models with iterative mask generation frameworks. However, we identify a persistent failure mode in current propose-then-select pipelines. Although high-quality mask candidates are often generated, the final prediction may fail to match the given linguistic condition. This failure arises because language semantics are typically used as static prompts or post-hoc matching signals, rather than participating in the iterative mask generation process. Through systematic analysis, we show that many errors stem from semantic misalignment rather than poor mask quality. To address this issue, we propose FlowSeg, which introduces dynamic semantic guidance via a bidirectional semantic flow between intermediate decoding states and LLM-derived condition embeddings throughout the generation process. Language conditions actively guide mask refinement at each stage, while condition embeddings are progressively updated by emerging visual evidence. This design yields semantically grounded mask representations and visually aligned language conditions, enabling more reliable matching. We further incorporate a lightweight boundary-aware refinement to selectively enhance uncertain regions without perturbing confident interiors. Extensive experiments on referring expression segmentation and reasoning segmentation tasks demonstrate that FlowSeg consistently improves language–mask alignment and achieves state-of-the-art performance.</p>","absKo":"<p>LLM-conditioned segmentation은 최근 large language models와 iterative mask generation framework를 결합하면서 빠르게 발전해 왔다. 그러나 우리는 현재의 propose-then-select pipeline에서 지속적으로 나타나는 failure mode를 확인했다. 고품질 mask candidate가 자주 생성되더라도, 최종 prediction이 주어진 linguistic condition과 일치하지 않을 수 있다. 이러한 실패는 language semantics가 iterative mask generation process에 참여하기보다는, 보통 static prompt나 post-hoc matching signal로만 사용되기 때문에 발생한다. 체계적인 분석을 통해, 많은 error가 poor mask quality보다 semantic misalignment에서 비롯됨을 보인다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 FlowSeg를 제안한다. FlowSeg는 generation 과정 전반에 걸쳐 intermediate decoding state와 LLM-derived condition embedding 사이의 bidirectional semantic flow를 통해 dynamic semantic guidance를 도입한다. language condition은 각 stage에서 mask refinement를 적극적으로 유도하며, condition embedding은 점진적으로 새롭게 나타나는 visual evidence에 의해 갱신된다. 이 설계는 semantically grounded한 mask representation과 visually aligned된 language condition을 만들어내어, 더 신뢰할 수 있는 matching을 가능하게 한다. 또한 우리는 boundary-aware refinement를 가볍게 통합하여, 확신이 높은 interior를 방해하지 않으면서 불확실한 region을 선택적으로 향상시킨다. referring expression segmentation과 reasoning segmentation task에 대한 광범위한 실험은 FlowSeg가 language–mask alignment를 일관되게 개선하고 state-of-the-art performance를 달성함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"63595","en":"FrameOracle: Learning What to See and How Much to See in Videos","ko":"FrameOracle: 비디오에서 무엇을 볼지와 얼마나 볼지 학습하기","authors":"Chaoyu Li, Tianzhi Li, Fei Tao, ZHENYU ZHAO, Ziqian Wu, Maozheng Zhao, Juntong Song, Cheng Niu, Pooyan Fazli","pos":"#1007","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Vd5bjrFQBh","abs":"<p>Vision-language models (VLMs) advance video understanding but operate under tight computational budgets, making performance dependent on selecting a small, high-quality subset of frames. Existing frame sampling strategies, such as uniform or fixed-budget selection, fail to adapt to variations in content density or task complexity. To address this, we present FrameOracle, a lightweight, plug-and-play module that predicts both (1) which frames are most relevant to a given query and (2) how many frames are needed. FrameOracle is trained via a curriculum that progresses from weak proxy signals, such as cross-modal similarity, to stronger supervision with FrameOracle-41K, the first large-scale VideoQA dataset with validated keyframe annotations specifying minimal sufficient frames per question. Extensive experiments across five VLMs and six benchmarks show that FrameOracle reduces 16-frame inputs to an average of 10.4 frames without accuracy loss. When starting from 64-frame candidates, it reduces inputs to 13.9 frames on average while improving accuracy by 1.5%, achieving state-of-the-art efficiency–accuracy trade-offs for scalable video understanding.</p>","absKo":"<p>Vision-language models (VLMs)는 video understanding을 발전시키지만, 엄격한 계산 예산 하에서 동작하므로 성능은 작은 고품질 frame subset을 선택하는 데 크게 좌우된다. uniform selection이나 fixed-budget selection 같은 기존 frame sampling strategy는 content density나 task complexity의 변화를 따라가지 못한다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 FrameOracle을 제시한다. 이는 가볍고 plug-and-play 방식의 module로, (1) 주어진 query와 가장 관련 있는 frame이 무엇인지와 (2) 몇 개의 frame이 필요한지를 함께 예측한다. FrameOracle은 weak proxy signal, 예를 들어 cross-modal similarity에서 시작해, 질문당 최소한으로 충분한 frame을 명시한 검증된 keyframe annotation을 포함하는 최초의 대규모 VideoQA dataset인 FrameOracle-41K로 더 강한 supervision으로 진행하는 curriculum을 통해 학습된다. 다섯 개의 VLM과 여섯 개의 benchmark에 걸친 대규모 실험은 FrameOracle이 16-frame input을 평균 10.4 frame으로 줄이면서도 정확도를 유지함을 보여준다. 64-frame 후보에서 시작할 때는 입력을 평균 13.9 frame으로 줄이면서 정확도를 1.5% 향상시켜, 확장 가능한 video understanding을 위한 state-of-the-art efficiency-accuracy trade-off를 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"60496","en":"From 2D Grids to 1D Tokens: Reforming Shared Representations for Multimodal Image Fusion","ko":"2D Grid에서 1D Token으로: Multimodal Image Fusion을 위한 Shared Representation 개편","authors":"Yuchen Xian, Yunqiu Xu, Yang He, Yi Yang","pos":"#1008","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=zjsvhm2QyV","abs":"<p>Multimodal image fusion (MMIF) aims to integrate complementary information from different modalities into a single fused image that preserves <em>fine local details</em> while maintaining <em>globally consistent appearance</em>. Most existing approaches build shared representations on 2D feature grids, which excel at modeling local structures but offer limited leverage over image-level appearance factors. To better optimize two objectives jointly, we redesign the shared representation by mapping inputs into a compact sequence of discrete <em>1D image tokens</em>, and instantiate this design with TiTok as a lightweight tokenizer, decoupling the shared representation from fixed pixel locations and concentrating image-level attributes into a small set of global tokens. We propose <em>Selective Token Editing</em> (STE): we sparsely update/replace only a small set of critical shared tokens, providing a lightweight token-level mechanism to steer global appearance coherence while keeping the fusion backbone unchanged and avoiding complex loss designs. Experiments on multiple benchmarks show that our method delivers <em>consistent, multi-metric improvements</em>—enhancing global coherence and local fidelity simultaneously—and achieves the <em>best overall performance</em> under comprehensive evaluation.</p>","absKo":"<p>Multimodal image fusion (MMIF)은 서로 다른 modality의 보완적 정보를 하나의 fused image로 통합하여 <em>fine local details</em>를 보존하면서도 <em>globally consistent appearance</em>를 유지하는 것을 목표로 한다. 기존의 대부분의 접근법은 2D feature grid 위에 shared representation을 구축하는데, 이는 local structure 모델링에는 뛰어나지만 image-level appearance factor를 활용하는 데는 한계가 있다. 두 목표를 더 잘 공동 최적화하기 위해, 우리는 입력을 이산적인 <em>1D image tokens</em>의 압축된 sequence로 매핑하도록 shared representation을 재설계하고, 이를 TiTok으로 경량 tokenizer 형태로 구현한다. 이를 통해 shared representation을 고정된 pixel location으로부터 분리하고 image-level attribute를 소수의 global token에 집중시킨다. 우리는 <em>Selective Token Editing</em> (STE)을 제안한다. 이는 소수의 핵심 shared token만 희소하게 업데이트/교체하는 방식으로, fusion backbone은 그대로 유지하면서 복잡한 loss design 없이 global appearance coherence를 조절하는 경량 token-level 메커니즘을 제공한다. 여러 benchmark에 대한 실험은 우리의 방법이 <em>consistent, multi-metric improvements</em>를 제공함을 보여준다. 즉, global coherence와 local fidelity를 동시에 향상시키며, 종합 평가에서 <em>best overall performance</em>를 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"60989","en":"Joint Geometric and Trajectory Consistency  Learning for One-Step Real-World Super-Resolution","ko":"원스텝 실제 환경 Super-Resolution을 위한 기하-궤적 공동 일관성 학습","authors":"Chengyan Deng, Zhangquan Chen, Li Yu, Kai Zhang, Xue Zhou, Wang Zhang","pos":"#1015","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ujZ7Swx14s","abs":"<p>Diffusion-based Real-World Image Super-Resolution (Real-ISR) achieves impressive perceptual quality but suffers from high computational costs due to iterative sampling. While recent distillation approaches leveraging large-scale Text-to-Image (T2I) priors have enabled one-step generation, they are typically hindered by prohibitive parameter counts and the inherent capability bounds imposed by teacher models. As a lightweight alternative, Consistency Models offer efficient inference but struggle with two critical limitations: the accumulation of consistency drift inherent to transitive training, and a phenomenon we term \"Geometric Decoupling\"— where the generative trajectory achieves pixel-wise alignment yet fails to preserve structural coherence. To address these challenges, we propose GTASR (Geometric Trajectory Alignment Super-Resolution), a {simple yet effective} consistency training paradigm for Real-ISR. Specifically, we introduce a Trajectory Alignment (TA) strategy to rectify the tangent vector field via full-path projection, and a Dual-Reference Structural Rectification (DRSR) mechanism to enforce strict structural constraints. Extensive experiments verify that GTASR delivers superior performance over representative baselines while maintaining minimal latency.</p>","absKo":"<p>Diffusion-based Real-World Image Super-Resolution (Real-ISR)은 뛰어난 perceptual quality를 달성하지만, iterative sampling으로 인해 계산 비용이 높다는 한계를 가진다. 최근 대규모 Text-to-Image (T2I) prior를 활용한 distillation 접근법은 one-step generation을 가능하게 했지만, 대개 과도한 parameter 수와 teacher model이 부과하는 본질적인 성능 한계에 의해 제약된다. 더 가벼운 대안으로 Consistency Model은 효율적인 inference를 제공하지만, transitive training에 내재된 consistency drift의 누적과, 우리가 \"Geometric Decoupling\"이라 부르는 현상이라는 두 가지 치명적인 한계에 부딪힌다. 이 현상에서는 생성 궤적이 pixel-wise alignment는 달성하지만 구조적 일관성(structural coherence)을 보존하지 못한다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 Real-ISR을 위한 {simple yet effective} consistency training paradigm인 GTASR (Geometric Trajectory Alignment Super-Resolution)을 제안한다. 구체적으로, 우리는 full-path projection을 통해 tangent vector field를 교정하는 Trajectory Alignment (TA) 전략과 엄격한 구조적 제약을 강제하는 Dual-Reference Structural Rectification (DRSR) 메커니즘을 도입한다. 광범위한 실험은 GTASR이 최소한의 latency를 유지하면서 대표적인 baseline보다 우수한 성능을 제공함을 검증한다.</p>"},{"id":"60526","en":"WorldCompass: Reinforcement Learning for Long-Horizon World Models","ko":"WorldCompass: Long-Horizon World Model을 위한 Reinforcement Learning","authors":"Zehan Wang, Tengfei Wang, Haiyu Zhang, Xuhui Zuo, Junta Wu, Haoyuan Wang, Wenqiang Sun, Zhenwei Wang, Chenjie Cao, Hengshuang Zhao, Chunchao Guo, Zhou Zhao","pos":"#108","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=zN8QDhuOHN","abs":"<p>This work presents WorldCompass, a novel Reinforcement Learning (RL) post-training framework for the long-horizon, interactive video-based world models, enabling them to explore the world more accurately and consistently based on interaction signals. To effectively \"steer\" the world model's exploration, we introduce three core innovations tailored to the autoregressive video generation paradigm: 1) Clip-level Roll-out Strategy: We generate and evaluate multiple samples at a single target clip, which significantly boosts roll-out efficiency and provides fine-grained reward signals. 2) Complementary Reward Functions: We design reward function for both interaction-following accuracy and visual quality, which provide direct supervision and effectively suppress reward-hacking behaviors. 3) Efficient RL Algorithm: We employ the negative-aware fine-tuning strategy coupled with various efficiency optimizations to efficiently and effectively enhance model capacity. Evaluations on the SoTA open-source world model, WorldPlay, demonstrate that WorldCompass significantly improves interaction accuracy and visual fidelity across various scenarios.</p>","absKo":"<p>본 연구는 장기 상호작용형 video-based world model을 위한 새로운 Reinforcement Learning (RL) post-training framework인 WorldCompass를 제시하며, 상호작용 신호에 기반해 세계를 더 정확하고 일관되게 탐색할 수 있게 한다. world model의 탐색을 효과적으로 \"steer\"하기 위해, 우리는 autoregressive video generation 패러다임에 맞춘 세 가지 핵심 혁신을 도입한다. 1) Clip-level Roll-out Strategy: 단일 target clip에서 여러 샘플을 생성하고 평가하여 roll-out 효율을 크게 높이고, 더 세밀한 reward signal을 제공한다. 2) Complementary Reward Functions: interaction-following accuracy와 visual quality 모두에 대한 reward function을 설계하여 직접적인 supervision을 제공하고 reward-hacking 행동을 효과적으로 억제한다. 3) Efficient RL Algorithm: negative-aware fine-tuning 전략과 다양한 효율화 최적화를 결합하여 모델 용량을 효율적이고 효과적으로 향상시킨다. 최첨단 open-source world model인 WorldPlay에서 수행한 평가 결과, WorldCompass는 다양한 시나리오에서 interaction accuracy와 visual fidelity를 크게 향상시킴을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"61522","en":"CSD: Content-aware Speculative Decoding for Efficient Image Generation","ko":"CSD: 효율적 이미지 생성을 위한 Content-Aware Speculative Decoding","authors":"Mingcheng Wang, junbo qiao, Yunchen Li, Lingfu Jiang, Wei Li, Jie Hu, Jiao Xie, Zhou Yu, Xinghao Chen, Guixu Zhang, Shaohui Lin","pos":"#1101","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=pJbip42zR6","abs":"<p>Speculative decoding (SD) has emerged as a key solution to accelerate the inference of autoregressive models. However, in the field of image generation, it faces the challenge of low acceptance rates, and directly relaxing its criteria leads to degradation in image quality. In this paper, we propose a novel content-aware speculative decoding algorithm, termed CSD, which integrates an entropy-based probability relaxation mechanism with an optimal resampling strategy to enhance the inference efficiency for autoregressive image generation. By leveraging the informational uncertainty inherent in different regions of an image, CSD dynamically adjusts the acceptance probability of candidate tokens, increasing the acceptance rate in low-detail areas to accelerate generation. Moreover, a distribution alignment filter is introduced to ensure the output distribution to be aligned with the target model, which significantly improves the generative quality. Experiments conducted on Lumina-mGPT and Janus-Pro demonstrate that the superiority of the proposed CSD. Our source codes are released in Supplementary Material.</p>","absKo":"<p>Speculative decoding (SD)는 autoregressive model의 inference를 가속하는 핵심 해법으로 부상했다. 그러나 image generation 분야에서는 낮은 acceptance rate라는 문제에 직면하며, 기준을 직접 완화하면 image quality가 저하된다. 본 논문에서는 entropy 기반 probability relaxation mechanism과 optimal resampling strategy를 결합하여 autoregressive image generation의 inference 효율을 높이는, content-aware speculative decoding algorithm인 CSD를 제안한다. 이미지의 서로 다른 영역에 내재한 정보적 불확실성을 활용해 CSD는 candidate token의 acceptance probability를 동적으로 조정하여, 세부 정보가 적은 영역에서는 acceptance rate를 높여 생성을 가속한다. 또한 output distribution이 target model과 정렬되도록 distribution alignment filter를 도입하여 generative quality를 크게 향상시킨다. Lumina-mGPT와 Janus-Pro에서 수행한 실험은 제안한 CSD의 우수성을 입증한다. 소스 코드는 Supplementary Material에 공개한다.</p>"},{"id":"63219","en":"Breaking the Synthetic-Real Domain Shortcut for Training-Free Generative Replay-based Class Incremental Learning","ko":"학습 불필요 생성적 재생 기반 클래스 증분 학습을 위한 합성-실제 도메인 지름길 파괴","authors":"Tao Zhang, Xu Zou, Qixuan Fan, Yiyuan Liang, Yanjie Wang, Song Yan, Tian Tian, Jiahuan Zhou, Luxin Yan, Sheng Zhong","pos":"#1104","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Z1HeVZNdMn","abs":"<p>Class-incremental learning (CIL) requires models to continuously acquire new knowledge while avoiding catastrophic forgetting. While exemplar replay is effective, it raises concerns regarding privacy and storage. Thus, generative replay has emerged as a viable alternative, synthesizing old data using frozen pretrained text-to-image (T2I) models without any extra training. However, we observe that directly mixing synthetic old-class data with real new-class data during incremental training leads to significant performance degradation. This issue stems from a ‘’domain shortcut'', where models rely on domain-discriminative features instead of semantic class cues. To address this, we propose DREAM (Domain-Regularized Exemplar-free Alignment Model), which uses a training-free generator to synthesize old-class data and eliminates domain shortcut via subspace rectification and orthogonal projection, while reinforcing semantic alignment through real-anchored prototype regularization. Extensive experiments on 4 datasets demonstrate that DREAM outperforms existing exemplar-free CIL methods and achieves state-of-the-art performance.</p>","absKo":"<p>Class-incremental learning(CIL)은 모델이 catastrophic forgetting을 피하면서 새로운 지식을 지속적으로 습득해야 한다. exemplar replay는 효과적이지만, privacy와 storage에 대한 우려를 낳는다. 따라서 generative replay는 추가 학습 없이 frozen pretrained text-to-image(T2I) model을 사용해 과거 데이터를 합성하는 실현 가능한 대안으로 부상했다. 그러나 우리는 incremental training 동안 synthetic old-class data와 real new-class data를 직접 혼합하면 성능이 크게 저하됨을 관찰했다. 이 문제는 모델이 semantic class cue 대신 domain-discriminative feature에 의존하는 ‘’domain shortcut''에서 비롯된다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 DREAM(Domain-Regularized Exemplar-free Alignment Model)을 제안한다. DREAM은 training-free generator를 사용해 old-class data를 합성하고, subspace rectification과 orthogonal projection을 통해 domain shortcut을 제거하는 한편, real-anchored prototype regularization으로 semantic alignment를 강화한다. 4개 데이터셋에 대한 광범위한 실험은 DREAM이 기존 exemplar-free CIL 방법들을 능가하고 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"62824","en":"Benchmarking and Enhancing VLM for Compressed Image Understanding","ko":"압축 이미지 이해를 위한 VLM 벤치마킹 및 강화","authors":"Zifu Zhang, Tongda Xu, Siqi Li, Shengxi Li, Yue Zhang, Mai Xu, Yan Wang","pos":"#1105","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=cvM6PcgOpS","abs":"<p>With the rapid development of Vision-Language Models (VLMs) and the growing demand for their applications, efficient compression of the image inputs has become increasingly important. Existing VLMs predominantly digest and understand high-bitrate compressed images, while their ability to interpret low-bitrate compressed images has yet to be explored by far. In this paper, we introduce the first comprehensive benchmark to evaluate the ability of VLM against compressed images, varying existing widely used image codecs and diverse set of tasks, encompassing over one million compressed images in our benchmark. Next, we analyse the source of performance gap, by categorising the gap from a) the information loss during compression and b) generalisation failure of VLM. We visualize these gaps with concrete examples and identify that for compressed images, only the generalization gap can be mitigated. Finally, we propose a universal VLM adaptor to enhance model performance on images compressed by existing codecs. Consequently, we demonstrate that a single adaptor can improve VLM performance across images with varying codecs and bitrates by 10%-30%. We believe that our benchmark and enhancement method provide valuable insights and contribute toward bridging the gap between VLMs and compressed images.</p>","absKo":"<p>Vision-Language Model(VLM)의 빠른 발전과 그 활용 수요의 증가로 인해, image input의 효율적인 compression이 점점 더 중요해지고 있다. 기존 VLM은 주로 높은 bitrate로 압축된 이미지를 처리하고 이해하는 데 초점을 맞추고 있으며, 낮은 bitrate로 압축된 이미지를 해석하는 능력은 아직 충분히 탐구되지 않았다. 본 논문에서는 널리 사용되는 다양한 image codec과 여러 task를 포괄하며, benchmark 내에 백만 개가 넘는 compressed image를 포함하는, compressed image에 대한 VLM의 능력을 평가하는 최초의 포괄적 benchmark를 소개한다. 다음으로, 우리는 성능 격차의 원인을 a) compression 과정에서의 information loss와 b) VLM의 generalization failure로 구분하여 분석한다. 이러한 격차를 구체적인 예시와 함께 시각화하고, compressed image의 경우 generalization gap만 완화될 수 있음을 확인한다. 마지막으로, 기존 codec으로 압축된 이미지에서 model performance를 향상시키기 위한 universal VLM adaptor를 제안한다. 그 결과, 하나의 adaptor만으로도 서로 다른 codec과 bitrate를 가진 이미지 전반에서 VLM performance를 10%-30% 향상시킬 수 있음을 보인다. 우리는 우리의 benchmark와 enhancement method가 VLM과 compressed image 사이의 간극을 메우는 데 유용한 통찰을 제공하고 기여하리라 믿는다.</p>"},{"id":"64848","en":"ScalingAR: Scaling Confidence for Autoregressive Image Generation","ko":"ScalingAR: Autoregressive 이미지 생성을 위한 Confidence 확장","authors":"Harold Haodong Chen, Xianfeng Wu, Wenjie Shu, Rongjin Guo, Disen Lan, Harry Yang, YINGCONG CHEN","pos":"#2506","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=JBEt767Naf","abs":"<p>Test-time strategies have shown remarkable success in improving large language models, but their application to next-token prediction (NTP) autoregressive (AR) image generation remains largely underexplored. Existing test-time scaling (TTS) methods for visual autoregressive models (VAR) rely on frequent partial decoding and external reward models, which are inefficient and often ineffective for NTP-based image generation due to the inherent instability of intermediate decoding results. To address these limitations, we propose <strong>ScalingAR</strong>, a novel test-time scaling framework tailored for NTP-based AR image generation. ScalingAR introduces <em>token entropy</em> as a confidence signal and operates at two complementary levels: (<em><strong>i</strong></em>) <em><strong>Profile Level</strong></em>, integrates intrinsic uncertainty and conditional utilization into a unified confidence state, and (<em><strong>ii</strong></em>) <em><strong>Policy Level</strong></em>, leverages this state for adaptive trajectory pruning and dynamic guidance scheduling. Without requiring early decoding or auxiliary rewards, ScalingAR achieves significant improvements across diverse benchmarks. Experiments show that ScalingAR <strong>(I)</strong> improves base models by 12.5% on GenEval and 15.2% on TIIF-Bench, <strong>(II)</strong> reduces visual token consumption by 62.0% while outperforming baselines, and <strong>(III)</strong> enhances robustness, mitigating performance degradation by 26.0% in challenging scenarios. These results establish \\ourmethod as a robust and efficient test-time scaling solution for autoregressive image generation.</p>"},{"id":"61031","en":"OmniShow: Orchestrating Multimodal Conditions for Human-Object Interaction Video Generation","ko":"OmniShow: 인간-객체 상호작용 비디오 생성을 위한 멀티모달 조건 조율","authors":"Donghao Zhou, Guisheng Liu, Hao Yang, Jiatong Li, Jingyu Lin, Xiaohu Huang, Yichen Liu, Xin Gao, Cunjian Chen, Shilei Wen, Chi Wing Fu, Pheng Ann Heng","pos":"#2514","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=uNWexq8gQB","abs":"<p>In this work, we study <strong>Human-Object Interaction Video Generation (HOIVG)</strong>, which aims to synthesize high-quality HOI videos via text, reference image, audio, and pose conditions. To address the challenges of harmonious multimodal injection and heterogeneous data utility, we present <strong>OmniShow</strong>, an end-to-end framework tailored for HOIVG. We introduce <em>Unified Channel-wise Conditioning</em> to efficiently inject image and pose cues, <em>Gated Local-Context Attention</em> to ensure precise audio-visual synchronization, and a <em>Decoupled-then-Joint Training strategy</em> to effectively harness heterogeneous data. Extensive experiments on the proposed <em>HOIVG-Bench</em> demonstrate that OmniShow achieves state-of-the-art performance.</p>","absKo":"<p>본 연구에서는 텍스트, reference image, audio, pose 조건을 통해 고품질 HOI 비디오를 합성하는 것을 목표로 하는 <strong>Human-Object Interaction Video Generation (HOIVG)</strong>을 연구한다. 조화로운 multimodal injection과 이질적인 데이터 효용의 문제를 해결하기 위해, HOIVG에 특화된 end-to-end 프레임워크인 <strong>OmniShow</strong>를 제안한다. 우리는 이미지와 pose 신호를 효율적으로 주입하기 위한 <em>Unified Channel-wise Conditioning</em>, 정확한 audio-visual synchronization을 보장하기 위한 <em>Gated Local-Context Attention</em>, 그리고 이질적인 데이터를 효과적으로 활용하기 위한 <em>Decoupled-then-Joint Training strategy</em>를 도입한다. 제안한 <em>HOIVG-Bench</em>에서 수행한 광범위한 실험은 OmniShow가 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"61470","en":"Hierarchical Image Tokenization for Multi-Scale Image Super Resolution","ko":"Multi-Scale Image Super Resolution을 위한 계층적 이미지 Tokenization","authors":"Isma Hadji, Enrique Sanchez, Adrian Bulat, Brais Martinez, Georgios Tzimiropoulos","pos":"#2610","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=prZKQmxXmq","abs":"<p>We introduce a multi-scale Image Super Resolution (ISR) method building on recent advances in Visual Auto-Regressive (VAR) modeling. Recently, VAR models challenged the dominance of diffusion-based models by adopting a next-scale prediction paradigm. Specifically, VAR models iteratively estimate the residual in latent space between gradually increasing image scales, an approach that aligns perfectly with our target ISR task. Previous work taking advantage of this synergy, suffer from two main shortcomings. First, due to the limitations of the residual quantizers used in VAR models, they typically only generate images at a predefined fixed scale, i.e. they fail to map intermediate outputs to the corresponding image scales. Also, to achieve better performance, they rely on large backbones and either external VLM for guidance, or a large corpus of external carefully annotated data. To address both shortcomings, we introduce two novel components to the VAR training for ISR, aiming at increasing its flexibility and reducing its complexity. In particular, we introduce a) a Hierarchical Image Tokenization (HIT) approach with a multi-scale image tokenizer that progressively represents images at different scales while enforcing token overlap across scales, and b) a Direct Preference Optimization (DPO) regularization term that, relying solely on the (LR,HR) pair, encourages the transformer to produce the latter over the former. The resulting model can denoise the LR image and super-resolve at different upscale factors in a single forward pass, and achieves state-of-the-art results using a relatively small model (300M params vs ~1B params of VARSR), and without the need of external training data.</p>","absKo":"<p>최근 발전한 Visual Auto-Regressive (VAR) 모델링을 기반으로 한 multi-scale Image Super Resolution (ISR) 방법을 소개한다. 최근 VAR 모델은 next-scale prediction 패러다임을 채택함으로써 diffusion 기반 모델의 우위를 도전했다. 구체적으로, VAR 모델은 점진적으로 증가하는 이미지 스케일 사이의 latent space에서 residual을 반복적으로 추정하는데, 이는 우리가 목표로 하는 ISR 작업과 정확히 부합한다. 이 시너지를 활용한 기존 연구들은 두 가지 주요 한계에 시달린다. 첫째, VAR 모델에서 사용되는 residual quantizer의 제약으로 인해, 보통 사전에 정의된 고정 스케일의 이미지만 생성할 수 있어 중간 출력과 대응하는 image scale을 매핑하지 못한다. 또한 더 나은 성능을 달성하기 위해 큰 backbone에 의존하고, 외부 VLM의 guidance 또는 대규모의 외부 정교한 주석 데이터 코퍼스에 의존한다. 이 두 한계를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 VAR의 ISR 학습에 두 가지 새로운 구성 요소를 도입하여 유연성을 높이고 복잡성을 줄이고자 한다. 구체적으로, a) 다양한 스케일의 이미지를 점진적으로 표현하면서 스케일 간 token overlap을 강제하는 multi-scale image tokenizer를 사용하는 Hierarchical Image Tokenization (HIT) 접근법과, b) (LR,HR) pair에만 의존하여 transformer가 LR보다 HR을 생성하도록 장려하는 Direct Preference Optimization (DPO) regularization term을 도입한다. 그 결과 모델은 단일 forward pass에서 LR 이미지를 denoise하고 다양한 upscale factor로 super-resolve할 수 있으며, 비교적 작은 모델(300M params 대 VARSR의 약 1B params)을 사용하면서도 external training data 없이 state-of-the-art 결과를 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"61737","en":"Advantage Weighted Matching: Aligning RL with Pretraining in Diffusion Models","ko":"Advantage Weighted Matching: Diffusion Model에서 RL과 Pretraining 정렬","authors":"Shuchen Xue, Chongjian GE, Shilong Zhang, Yichen Li, Zhi-Ming Ma","pos":"#2702","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=nLY2pOYBrJ","abs":"Reinforcement Learning (RL) has emerged as a central paradigm for advancing Large Language Models (LLMs), where both pre-training and RL post-training stages are grounded in the same log-likelihood formulation. In contrast, recent RL approaches for diffusion models, most notably Denoising Diffusion Policy Optimization (DDPO), optimize an objective different from the pretraining objectives--score/flow matching loss. In this work, we establish a novel theoretical analysis: DDPO is an implicit form of score/flow matching with noisy targets, which increases variance and slows convergence. Building on this analysis, we introduce Advantage Weighted Matching (AWM), a policy-gradient method for diffusion. It uses the score/flow-matching loss and reweights each sample by its advantage. In effect, AWM raises the influence of high-reward samples and suppresses low-reward ones while keeping the modeling objective identical to pretraining. This unifies pretraining and RL conceptually and practically and reduces variance, yielding faster convergence. This simple yet effective design yields substantial benefits: on the GenEval, OCR, and PickScore benchmarks, AWM delivers up to a $34\\times$ speedup over Flow-GRPO (which builds on DDPO), when applied to Stable Diffusion 3.5 Medium and FLUX, without compromising generation quality. Code is provided in the supplementary material.","absKo":"Reinforcement Learning(RL)은 Large Language Models(LLMs) 발전의 핵심 패러다임으로 부상했으며, pre-training과 RL post-training 단계 모두 같은 log-likelihood formulation에 기반한다. 이와 대조적으로, diffusion model을 위한 최근 RL 접근법, 특히 Denoising Diffusion Policy Optimization(DDPO)은 pretraining objective와 다른 objective를 최적화한다. 구체적으로 score/flow matching loss이다. 본 연구에서는 새로운 이론적 분석을 확립한다. DDPO는 noisy target을 사용하는 score/flow matching의 implicit form이며, 이로 인해 variance가 증가하고 convergence가 느려진다. 이러한 분석을 바탕으로 우리는 diffusion을 위한 policy-gradient method인 Advantage Weighted Matching(AWM)을 제안한다. AWM은 score/flow-matching loss를 사용하고, 각 sample을 그 advantage로 reweight한다. 결과적으로 AWM은 모델링 objective를 pretraining과 동일하게 유지하면서 high-reward sample의 영향을 높이고 low-reward sample의 영향을 억제한다. 이는 pretraining과 RL을 개념적으로도 실용적으로도 통합하며, variance를 줄여 더 빠른 convergence를 이끈다. 이 단순하지만 효과적인 설계는 상당한 이점을 제공한다. GenEval, OCR, PickScore benchmark에서 AWM은 Stable Diffusion 3.5 Medium과 FLUX에 적용했을 때, 생성 품질을 저하시키지 않으면서 Flow-GRPO(DDPO 위에 구축됨) 대비 최대 $34\\times$의 속도 향상을 달성한다. 코드는 supplementary material에 제공된다."},{"id":"64473","en":"TAGRPO: Boosting GRPO on Image-to-Video Generation with Direct Trajectory Alignment","ko":"TAGRPO: 직접 궤적 정렬을 통한 Image-to-Video 생성에서 GRPO 강화","authors":"Jin Wang, Jianxiang Lu, Xu Guangzheng, Comi Chen, Haoyu Yang, zhenzhen qin, Peng Chen, Mingtao Chen, Zhichao hu, Longhuang Wu, Shuai Shao, Qinglin Lu, Ping Luo","pos":"#2805","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=NEiMxuUCSc","abs":"<p>Recent studies have demonstrated the efficacy of integrating Group Relative Policy Optimization (GRPO) into flow matching models, particularly for text-to-image and text-to-video generation. However, we find that directly applying these techniques to image-to-video (I2V) models often fails to yield consistent reward improvements. To address this limitation, we present TAGRPO, a robust post-training framework for I2V models inspired by contrastive learning. Our approach is grounded in the observation that rollout videos generated from identical initial noise provide superior guidance for optimization. Leveraging this insight, we propose a novel GRPO loss applied to intermediate latents, encouraging direct alignment with high-reward trajectories while maximizing distance from low-reward counterparts. Furthermore, we introduce a memory bank for rollout videos to enhance diversity and reduce computational overhead. Despite its simplicity, TAGRPO achieves significant improvements over DanceGRPO in I2V generation. Code and models will be made publicly available.</p>","absKo":"<p>최근 연구들은 Group Relative Policy Optimization (GRPO)을 flow matching 모델에 통합하는 것이 특히 text-to-image 및 text-to-video 생성에서 효과적임을 보여주었다. 그러나 우리는 이러한 기법을 image-to-video (I2V) 모델에 직접 적용하면 일관된 reward 향상을 얻지 못하는 경우가 많다는 것을 발견했다. 이러한 한계를 해결하기 위해, contrastive learning에서 영감을 받은 I2V 모델용 견고한 post-training framework인 TAGRPO를 제안한다. 우리의 접근은 동일한 초기 noise에서 생성된 rollout video가 최적화에 더 우수한 guidance를 제공한다는 관찰에 기반한다. 이 통찰을 활용하여, 우리는 intermediate latent에 적용되는 새로운 GRPO loss를 제안하며, 높은 reward trajectory와의 직접적인 정렬을 촉진하는 동시에 낮은 reward trajectory와의 거리를 최대화한다. 또한 rollout video를 위한 memory bank를 도입하여 다양성을 높이고 계산 오버헤드를 줄인다. 단순함에도 불구하고 TAGRPO는 I2V 생성에서 DanceGRPO를 크게 능가하는 성능을 달성한다. 코드와 모델은 공개될 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"62091","en":"Video-SVD: Efficient Video Diffusion via Orthogonal Basis Composition","ko":"Video-SVD: 직교 기저 합성을 통한 효율적 비디오 Diffusion","authors":"Zhang Wan, Yu Li, Tianze Huang, Haochen Li, Juan Cao, Sheng Tang","pos":"#2904","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=jsqpBopQuS","abs":"Video Diffusion Transformers (VDiTs) represent the state-of-the-art in video generation but are fundamentally constrained by the quadratic computational complexity of self-attention. To accelerate this critical computation, we analyze the pre-softmax matrix ($QK^T$) and reveal two key insights: (1) dense attention patterns inherently reside on a global low-rank manifold characterized by rapid singular value decay; and (2) real motion manifests as hybrid spatio-temporal patterns rather than rigid \"spatial vs. temporal\" classifications. Guided by these insights, we propose Video-SVD. As a plug-and-play acceleration method that requires no alteration to the original network parameters, it extracts universal bases via offline SVD and employs a dynamic subspace projection strategy at inference, thereby bypassing the expensive full $QK^T$ matrix computation entirely. To ensure high fidelity, we deploy layer-shared dual-stream MLPs to synthesize fine-grained textural details and recover high-frequency RoPE information. Video-SVD achieves significant end-to-end speedup while maintaining high visual quality, reaching 1.92$\\times$ on HunyuanVideo, 1.75$\\times$ on Wan2.1-1.3B, and 1.79$\\times$ on Wan2.1-14B.","absKo":"Video Diffusion Transformer(VDiT)는 video generation에서 state-of-the-art를 대표하지만, self-attention의 이차적 계산 복잡도라는 근본적 제약을 받는다. 이 핵심 계산을 가속화하기 위해 우리는 pre-softmax matrix($QK^T$)를 분석하여 두 가지 핵심 통찰을 도출한다: (1) dense attention pattern은 빠른 singular value decay로 특징지어지는 전역 저랭크 manifold 위에 본질적으로 존재하며, (2) 실제 motion은 엄격한 \"spatial 대 temporal\" 분류가 아니라 hybrid spatio-temporal pattern으로 나타난다. 이러한 통찰에 따라 우리는 Video-SVD를 제안한다. 원래 network parameter를 변경할 필요가 없는 plug-and-play 가속 방법으로서, offline SVD를 통해 universal basis를 추출하고 inference 시 dynamic subspace projection strategy를 사용함으로써 비용이 큰 full $QK^T$ matrix 계산을 완전히 우회한다. 높은 fidelity를 보장하기 위해 우리는 layer-shared dual-stream MLP를 사용하여 미세한 texture detail을 합성하고 high-frequency RoPE 정보를 복원한다. Video-SVD는 높은 visual quality를 유지하면서도 종단 간 속도를 크게 향상시키며, HunyuanVideo에서 1.92$\\times$, Wan2.1-1.3B에서 1.75$\\times$, Wan2.1-14B에서 1.79$\\times$를 달성한다."},{"id":"62336","en":"LieWarper: Geometry-Aware Motion Transfer via Lie Algebra","ko":"LieWarper: Lie Algebra 기반 Geometry-Aware Motion Transfer","authors":"Linsong Shan, Laurence Yang, Zecan Yang, Fukai Guo, Honglu Zhao, Yixuan Geng","pos":"#3614","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=hYQQgQWPgJ","abs":"Video motion transfer aims to synthesize novel content videos that strictly follow the motion trajectories of a reference video. However, existing methods typically operate in Euclidean space, treating motion as unconstrained pixel displacements or linear phase shifts. This simplification frequently causes severe shearing artifacts and perspective collapse under complex camera and object motions. In this work, we present LieWarper, a geometry-aware motion transfer framework that reconceptualizes motion as coordinate evolution on a manifold rather than mere pixel displacement. Specifically, we derive an analytic solver on the $\\text{Sim}(2)$ manifold to extract global evolution parameters from noisy optical flow. We then introduce a flow-guided phase modulation mechanism, enabling non-rigid dynamics to undergo coordinate transformation along the evolution path. This approach achieves accurate trajectory transfer while maintaining global geometric integrity. Extensive experiments show that LieWarper significantly outperforms state-of-the-art training-free baselines in both motion fidelity and geometric stability, while maintaining high generation quality.","absKo":"Video motion transfer는 reference video의 motion trajectory를 엄격히 따르는 새로운 content video를 합성하는 것을 목표로 한다. 그러나 기존 방법은 대체로 Euclidean space에서 작동하며, motion을 제약 없는 pixel displacement 또는 선형 phase shift로 취급한다. 이러한 단순화는 복잡한 camera 및 object motion 하에서 심각한 shearing artifact와 perspective collapse를 자주 유발한다. 본 연구에서는 motion을 단순한 pixel displacement가 아니라 manifold 위의 coordinate evolution으로 재개념화하는 geometry-aware motion transfer framework인 LieWarper를 제시한다. 구체적으로, 우리는 잡음이 섞인 optical flow로부터 global evolution parameter를 추출하기 위해 $\\text{Sim}(2)$ manifold 위의 analytic solver를 유도한다. 이어서 flow-guided phase modulation mechanism을 도입하여 비강체(non-rigid) dynamics가 evolution path를 따라 coordinate transformation을 수행하도록 한다. 이 접근법은 global geometric integrity를 유지하면서 정확한 trajectory transfer를 달성한다. 광범위한 실험은 LieWarper가 motion fidelity와 geometric stability 모두에서 state-of-the-art training-free baseline을 크게 능가하면서도 높은 generation quality를 유지함을 보여준다."},{"id":"64504","en":"SCoA: Revisiting Domain Generalized Object Detection with Style-Conditioned Adaptation","ko":"SCoA: 스타일 조건 적응을 통한 도메인 일반화 객체 탐지 재고","authors":"Han Jiang, Wenfei Yang, Tianzhu Zhang, Yongdong Zhang","pos":"#800","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=MtoQFUksrQ","abs":"<p>Domain generalized object detection (DGOD) aims to train an object detector on a single source domain and generalize it to  unseen  target domains.  Recent advances in DGOD have increasingly exploited vision foundation models (VFMs) via parameter-efficient finetuning strategies. However, existing approaches typically adapt VFMs with fixed, style-agnostic parameters, overlooking that different visual styles may induce distinct task discrepancies. To address this challenge, we propose  SCoA, a novel  Style  Conditioned  Adaptation framework for dynamic, style-aware task compensation.  Specifically, we introduce a Spectral Style Modeling (SSM) module that preserves local style cues via a memory-based mechanism, enabling diverse style characterization from a single source domain. Conditioned on the extracted style signals, we design a Mixture-of-Tokens Adaptation (MTA) mechanism, which maintains multiple adaptation tokens and dynamically routes each sample to an optimal combination of tokens, thereby explicitly modeling style-dependent task mismatches. In addition, we propose a Style-Conditioned Query Refinement (SCQR) module that injects style information into object queries,  enabling a style-aware detection head. By jointly integrating these components, SCoA allows the model to follow style-specific adaptation trajectories, achieving effective and flexible task compensation for VFM-based DGOD. Extensive experiments demonstrate that the proposed SCoA  achieves state-of-the-art performance across two challenging scenarios.</p>","absKo":"<p>Domain generalized object detection (DGOD)는 단일 source domain에서 object detector를 학습시킨 뒤 보지 못한 target domain으로 일반화하는 것을 목표로 한다. 최근 DGOD의 발전은 parameter-efficient finetuning 전략을 통해 vision foundation model (VFM)을 적극 활용하고 있다. 그러나 기존 접근법은 보통 고정된, style-agnostic parameter로 VFM을 적응시키며, 서로 다른 visual style이 서로 다른 task discrepancy를 유발할 수 있다는 점은 간과한다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 동적이고 style-aware한 task compensation을 위한 새로운 Style Conditioned Adaptation 프레임워크인 SCoA를 제안한다. 구체적으로, 우리는 memory-based mechanism을 통해 local style cue를 보존하는 Spectral Style Modeling (SSM) 모듈을 도입하여, 단일 source domain으로부터 다양한 style characterization을 가능하게 한다. 추출된 style signal을 조건으로, 우리는 Mixture-of-Tokens Adaptation (MTA) 메커니즘을 설계하여 여러 adaptation token을 유지하고 각 sample을 token의 최적 조합으로 동적으로 라우팅함으로써 style-dependent task mismatch를 명시적으로 모델링한다. 더불어, 우리는 style 정보를 object query에 주입하는 Style-Conditioned Query Refinement (SCQR) 모듈을 제안하여 style-aware detection head를 가능하게 한다. 이러한 구성요소들을 공동으로 통합함으로써, SCoA는 model이 style-specific adaptation trajectory를 따르도록 하여, VFM-based DGOD에서 효과적이고 유연한 task compensation을 달성한다. 광범위한 실험은 제안한 SCoA가 두 가지 까다로운 시나리오 전반에서 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"62352","en":"Temporal-aware Flow Matching for Video Generation with Temporally Coherent Motion","ko":"시간적으로 일관된 운동을 갖는 비디오 생성용 Temporal-aware Flow Matching","authors":"Zirui Pan, Xin Wang, Yipeng Zhang, Yuwei Zhou, Wenwu Zhu","pos":"#808","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=hPIOKm727h","abs":"<p>Despite rapid advances in text-to-video generation, state-of-the-art generative models still suffer from producing temporally incoherent and unrealistic motion for videos. The key weakness of existing works is that they commonly treat videos as frame sequences and directly adopt Flow Matching objectives, which are originally designed for images. This practice fails to explicitly model motion priors or temporal dependencies, resulting in suboptimal dynamics that may appear incoherent and unrealistic. To solve this problem, we propose Temporal-aware Flow Matching (TFM), a novel training paradigm that embeds inter-frame constraints into the flow objective, leading to temporally coherent motion modeling in video generation. More specifically, the proposed TFM enforces temporal correlations across frames while retaining the desirable properties of Flow Matching, and further introduces a residual-type loss that aligns naturally with this new flow. We theoretically prove that models trained with TFM are able to exhibit remarkably enhanced temporal perception ability and better capture motion dynamics. Notably, TFM imposes no additional cost during inference and is applicable to any model using Flow Matching. Extensive experiments demonstrate that our TFM can significantly improve motion realism across diverse motion types. Generated videos are presented at https://tfm-2026.github.io.</p>","absKo":"<p>텍스트-비디오 생성이 빠르게 발전했음에도, 최첨단 생성 모델은 여전히 비디오에서 시간적으로 일관되지 않고 비현실적인 움직임을 만들어내는 문제를 겪고 있다. 기존 연구의 핵심 약점은 비디오를 일반적으로 프레임 시퀀스로 취급하고, 원래 이미지용으로 설계된 Flow Matching 목적함수를 직접 적용한다는 점이다. 이러한 관행은 motion prior나 temporal dependency를 명시적으로 모델링하지 못해, 결과적으로 일관성이 떨어지고 비현실적으로 보일 수 있는 최적화되지 않은 dynamics를 초래한다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 Temporal-aware Flow Matching(TFM)을 제안한다. TFM은 inter-frame constraint를 flow objective에 내재화하는 새로운 training paradigm으로, 비디오 생성에서 시간적으로 일관된 motion modeling을 이끈다. 보다 구체적으로, 제안하는 TFM은 Flow Matching의 바람직한 특성을 유지하면서 프레임 간 temporal correlation을 강제하고, 더 나아가 이 새로운 flow와 자연스럽게 정렬되는 residual-type loss를 도입한다. 우리는 TFM으로 학습된 모델이 현저히 향상된 temporal perception ability를 보이며 motion dynamics를 더 잘 포착할 수 있음을 이론적으로 증명한다. 특히 TFM은 추론 시 추가 비용을 전혀 요구하지 않으며, Flow Matching을 사용하는 어떤 모델에도 적용 가능하다. 광범위한 실험은 우리의 TFM이 다양한 motion type 전반에서 motion realism을 크게 향상시킬 수 있음을 보여준다. 생성된 비디오는 https://tfm-2026.github.io 에서 확인할 수 있다.</p>"},{"id":"62260","en":"TurboGS: Accelerating 3D Gaussian Splatting via Error-Guided Sparse Pixel Sampling and Optimization","ko":"TurboGS: Error-Guided Sparse Pixel Sampling 및 최적화를 통한 3D Gaussian Splatting 가속","authors":"Zheng Dong, Daifei Qiu, Pinxuan Dai, Ke Xu, Jiamin Xu, Lili He, Rynson Lau, Weiwei Xu","pos":"#809","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=iD88HhWBGc","abs":"<p>Consumer-level applications require fast optimization of 3D Gaussian Splatting (3DGS) with high-fidelity novel view rendering. However, existing 3DGS acceleration approaches still incur substantial computation on redundant pixels while sacrificing fine details. In this paper, we present TurboGS, an error-guided training framework that accelerates 3DGS by concentrating optimization on perceptually informative pixels. TurboGS is built upon four core components: (1) a tile-wise sparse pixel sampling, which, driven by multi-view reconstruction errors during training, prioritizes challenging regions and skips well-reconstructed ones to avoid redundant gradient computation; (2) a tile-wise structure-aware loss with sparse Normalized Cross-Correlation, which provides sparse yet effective supervision to preserve fine details and stabilize training; (3) an error-driven Gaussian density control strategy, which dynamically allocates model capacity and removes redundant primitives; and (4) a tailored hybrid optimizer that couples Hessian-informed updates with Adam moment damping to stabilize and improve convergence under sparse supervision. Experiments on standard benchmarks demonstrate that TurboGS can deliver on par or superior rendering quality within 100 seconds (up to 10x training speedup over vanilla 3DGS).</p>","absKo":"<p>소비자 수준의 애플리케이션에서는 high-fidelity novel view rendering을 제공하면서도 3D Gaussian Splatting(3DGS)을 빠르게 최적화할 수 있어야 한다. 그러나 기존의 3DGS 가속 기법은 세밀한 디테일을 희생하면서도 여전히 상당한 연산을 중복 픽셀에 사용한다. 본 논문에서는 지각적으로 정보가 풍부한 픽셀에 최적화를 집중시켜 3DGS를 가속하는 error-guided training framework인 TurboGS를 제안한다. TurboGS는 네 가지 핵심 구성요소로 이루어진다: (1) multi-view reconstruction error에 의해 구동되는 tile-wise sparse pixel sampling으로, 학습 중 어려운 영역을 우선시하고 잘 복원된 영역은 건너뛰어 중복 gradient computation을 피한다; (2) sparse Normalized Cross-Correlation을 사용하는 tile-wise structure-aware loss로, 세밀한 디테일을 보존하고 학습을 안정화하는 희소하지만 효과적인 supervision을 제공한다; (3) error-driven Gaussian density control strategy로, 모델 용량을 동적으로 할당하고 중복 primitive를 제거한다; (4) Hessian-informed update와 Adam moment damping을 결합한 맞춤형 hybrid optimizer로, 희소한 supervision 하에서의 수렴을 안정화하고 개선한다. 표준 benchmark 실험 결과, TurboGS는 100초 이내에 동급 또는 그 이상의 rendering quality를 제공할 수 있으며(vanilla 3DGS 대비 최대 10배 학습 속도 향상).</p>"},{"id":"65333","en":"Unified Multimodal Visual Tracking with Dual Mixture-of-Experts","ko":"Dual Mixture-of-Experts를 이용한 통합 멀티모달 시각 추적","authors":"Lingyi Hong, Jinglun Li, Xinyu Zhou, Kaixun Jiang, Pinxue Guo, Zhaoyu Chen, Runze Li, Xingdong Sheng, Wenqiang Zhang","pos":"#810","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Eeo0uBd5mt","abs":"<p>Multimodal visual object tracking can be divided into to several kinds of tasks (e.g. RGB and RGB+X tracking), based on the input modality. Existing methods often train separate models for each modality or rely on pretrained models to adapt to new modalities, which limits efficiency, scalability, and usability. Thus, we introduce OneTrackerV2, a unified multi-modal tracking framework that enables end-to-end training for any modality. We propose Meta Merger to embed multi-modal information into a unified space, allowing flexible modality fusion and improved robustness to corrupted modalities. We further introduce Dual Mixture-of-Experts (DMoE): T-MoE models spatio-temporal relations for tracking, while M-MoE embeds multi-modal knowledge, disentangling cross-modal dependencies and reducing feature conflicts. With a shared architecture, unified parameters, and a single end-to-end training, OneTrackerV2 achieves state-of-the-art performance across five RGB and RGB+X tracking tasks and 12 benchmarks, while maintaining high inference efficiency. Notably, even after model compression, OneTrackerV2 retains strong performance. Moreover, OneTrackerV2 demonstrates remarkable robustness under modality-missing scenarios.</p>"},{"id":"66151","en":"Video-in-the-Loop: Span-Grounded Long Video QA with Interleaved Reasoning","ko":"Video-in-the-Loop: 교차 추론을 통한 구간 기반 장편 비디오 QA","authors":"Chendong Wang, Donglin Bai, Yifan Yang, Xiao Jin, Anlan Zhang, Rui Wang, Shiqi Jiang, Yuqing Yang, Hao Wu, Qi Dai, Chong Luo, Ting Cao, Lili Qiu, Suman Banerjee","pos":"#812","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=6NDxn4R4JT","abs":"We present $\\textit{Video-in-the-Loop}$ (ViTL), a two-stage long-video QA framework that preserves a fixed token budget by first $\\textit{localizing}$ question-relevant interval(s) with a low-fps skim and then $\\textit{answering}$ via span-aware reallocation of visual tokens at higher effective frame rate, emitting an interleaved output with both spans and the final option for direct attribution. We also introduce $\\textit{VGrounding-QA}$, which converts description based event graphs into $\\textit{span-grounded}$ multiple-choice QA by pairing each question with $\\textit{ground-truth}$ time span(s) and related reasoning. ViTL is trained end-to-end with an interleaved group-relative objective that couples temporal IoU for localization with answer correctness, allowing credit to flow from answers back to spans without increasing compute. Under fixed token budgets, ViTL attains up to 8.6\\% with 50\\% less frame input on long-video QA and temporal grounding (e.g., Charades-STA, ActivityNet-Captions) and ablations show that span-aware token reallocation consistently surpasses uniform sampling. Together, $\\textit{VGrounding-QA}$ and ViTL provide an interpretable, compute-efficient recipe for scalable long-video QA."},{"id":"66375","en":"Resolution as a Direction: Vector-Panning Feature Alignment for Cross-Resolution Re-Identification","ko":"방향으로서의 해상도: 교차 해상도 재식별을 위한 벡터 패닝 특징 정렬","authors":"Zanwu Liu, Chao Yuan, Bo Li, Xiaowei Zhang, Guanglin Niu","pos":"#901","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=4FVs0ExC7m","abs":"<p>Cross-resolution person re-identification (CR-ReID) remains challenging in practical surveillance, where camera quality and capture distance lead to substantial resolution gaps between low-resolution (LR) queries and high-resolution (HR) gallery images. Prior approaches commonly rely on super-resolution (SR) or resolution-invariant representation learning, which often increases system complexity and may not directly address the feature mismatch induced by resolution degradation. In this work, we report a new empirical finding: after averaging out identity-specific variation, the HR--LR feature discrepancy produced by standard ReID backbones exhibits a consistent, resolution-related semantic direction in the embedding space. We further support this observation with statistical analyses based on Canonical Correlation Analysis (CCA) and Pearson correlation analysis. Motivated by this finding, we propose Vector Panning Feature Alignment (VPFA), a lightweight post-hoc module that learns to pan LR features along the learned resolution direction to obtain pseudo-HR representations. VPFA operates after feature extraction and can be integrated into existing ReID systems with negligible overhead. Extensive experiments on multiple CR-ReID benchmarks show that VPFA achieves state-of-the-art performance while improving efficiency compared to SR-based or jointly trained alternatives.</p>"},{"id":"65892","en":"RVAS: Referring Video Active Exploration and Segmentation","ko":"RVAS: 참조 영상 능동 탐색 및 분할","authors":"Hengrui Hu, Weiwei Gao, Zipei Zhang, Henghui Ding","pos":"#903","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=95wIQ6actx","abs":"<p>Existing referring video object segmentation (RVOS) is largely built on passive perception and assumes the target is already visible in the observed video, which limits real-world use when queries refer to objects beyond the current view. To address this gap, we introduce <strong>Referring Video Active Exploration and Segmentation</strong> (<strong>RVAS</strong>), a new task that focuses on reasoning about exploration policy and then locating and segmenting the object according to an input referring expression. To support RVAS, we build a large-scale dataset with manually annotated exploration actions and reference reasoning traces, enabling supervised training and evaluation. We benchmark representative RVOS and related video understanding baselines and find that they struggle to perform active target search and incur substantial overhead when coupled with online decision making. Motivated by these challenges, we propose LESA, a baseline framework that introduces a state controller and hierarchical memory for efficient streaming processing and sparse MLLM reasoning. LESA substantially reduces inference cost while maintaining competitive planning quality, and consistently improves segmentation accuracy on the RVAS dataset.</p>"},{"id":"66222","en":"Physics in 2-Steps: Locking Motion Priors Before Visual Refinement Erases Them","ko":"2단계 물리: 시각적 정제가 지우기 전에 운동 사전 지식을 고정하기","authors":"Woojung Han, Seil Kang, Youngjun Jun, Min-Hung Chen, Fu-En Yang, Seong Jae Hwang","pos":"#905","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=5f2hxtNqpM","abs":"Video diffusion models can generate visually stunning content, yet frequently produce motion that violates physical laws, objects accelerate implausibly or vanish mid-trajectory. We reveal a surprising finding: a 2-step generation often exhibits better physical consistency than a 50-step output from the same model. Through spectral analysis, we trace this to phase erosion during denoising, motion dynamics are $8.5\\times$ more sensitive to phase corruption than magnitude, yet the refinement process progressively destroys this critical component. Building on this insight, we propose PhaseLock, a training-free framework that locks motion dynamics to fast inference priors.  Rather than requiring 50 steps to establish physics, PhaseLock extracts a motion prior from just 2 steps and enforces it onto high-fidelity generation via Latent Delta Guidance. This decouples physical consistency from visual refinement, ensuring the final output remains grounded in valid trajectories. PhaseLock achieves strong physical consistency with negligible overhead ($1.06\\times$ time, $1.02\\times$ memory), eliminating the need for expensive external guidance methods ($\\sim5\\times$ time)."},{"id":"62888","en":"PhoStream: Benchmarking Real-World Streaming for Omnimodal Assistants in Mobile Scenarios","ko":"PhoStream: 모바일 환경에서 Omnimodal Assistant의 실세계 스트리밍 벤치마킹","authors":"Xudong LU, Guan Huankang, Yang Bo, Jinpeng Chen, Xintong Guo, Shuhan LI, Fang Liu, Peiwen Sun, Xueying Lee, Wei Zhang, Xue Yang, Rui Liu, Hongsheng Li","pos":"#906","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=cCMbxJcDmH","abs":"<p>Multimodal Large Language Models excel at offline audio-visual understanding, but their ability to serve as mobile assistants in continuous real-world streams remains underexplored. In daily phone use, mobile assistants must track streaming audio-visual inputs and respond at the right time, yet existing benchmarks are often restricted to multiple-choice questions or use shorter videos. In this paper, we introduce <strong>PhoStream</strong>, the first mobile-centric streaming benchmark that unifies on-screen and off-screen scenarios to evaluate video, audio, and temporal reasoning. PhoStream contains 5,572 open-ended QA pairs from 578 videos across 4 scenarios and 10 capabilities. We build it with an Automated Generative Pipeline backed by rigorous human verification, and evaluate models using a realistic Online Inference Pipeline and LLM-as-a-Judge evaluation for open-ended responses. Experiments reveal a temporal asymmetry in LLM-judged scores (0-100): models perform well on Instant and Backward tasks (Gemini 3 Pro exceeds 80), but drop sharply on Forward tasks (16.40), largely due to early responses before the required visual and audio cues appear. This highlights a fundamental limitation: current MLLMs struggle to decide <em><strong>when</strong></em> to speak, not just <em><strong>what</strong></em> to say.</p>","absKo":"<p>Multimodal Large Language Models는 offline audio-visual understanding에서는 뛰어나지만, continuous real-world stream에서 mobile assistant로서 얼마나 잘 기능하는지는 아직 충분히 탐구되지 않았다. 일상적인 휴대폰 사용에서 모바일 assistant는 streaming audio-visual input을 추적하고 적절한 시점에 응답해야 하지만, 기존 benchmark는 대개 multiple-choice question에 제한되거나 더 짧은 video를 사용한다. 이 논문에서는 video, audio, temporal reasoning을 함께 평가하기 위해 on-screen과 off-screen 시나리오를 통합한 최초의 mobile-centric streaming benchmark인 <strong>PhoStream</strong>을 소개한다. PhoStream은 4개 시나리오와 10개 capability에 걸친 578개 video로부터 얻은 5,572개의 open-ended QA pair를 포함한다. 우리는 엄격한 human verification을 뒷받침하는 Automated Generative Pipeline으로 이를 구축했으며, open-ended response에 대해서는 현실적인 Online Inference Pipeline과 LLM-as-a-Judge evaluation으로 model을 평가한다. 실험 결과, LLM-judged score(0-100)에서 temporal asymmetry가 드러난다. 모델은 Instant와 Backward task에서는 잘 수행하여 Gemini 3 Pro가 80을 넘지만, 필요한 visual 및 audio cue가 나타나기 전에 조기 응답을 하는 탓에 Forward task에서는 16.40까지 급격히 떨어진다. 이는 현재 MLLM의 근본적 한계가 단지 <em><strong>무엇을</strong></em> 말할지뿐 아니라 <em><strong>언제</strong></em> 말할지를 결정하는 데 있음을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"65362","en":"PMSPO: Progressive Matching and Semantic-Aware Policy Optimization for Camouflaged Object Detection","ko":"PMSPO: 위장 객체 탐지를 위한 점진적 매칭 및 의미 인지 정책 최적화","authors":"Maosheng Su, Junlei Cao, Zhiyuan Wang, Shuo Wang, Ning Zhang, Jun Luo","pos":"#908","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=EN086kcFBF","abs":"<p>Reinforcement learning-based Multimodal Large Language Models (MLLMs) provide new perspectives for visual grounding, yet face significant challenges in Camouflaged Object Detection (COD) where objects blend seamlessly with backgrounds. This stems primarily from: difficulties in multi-object matching, the detrimental effects of low-quality samples, and erroneously localizing visual distractors with similar textures to true objects. We propose Progressive Matching and Semantic-aware Policy Optimization (PMSPO), a curriculum learning-based framework that employs Sinkhorn multi-object matching IoU reward during training for multi-object alignment, utilizes Positive Learning Gain Filtering (PLGF) to curate high-quality samples, and transforms deep visual features into semantic contrastive reward rules to calibrate target background semantics. Experiments on COD benchmarks demonstrate that PMSPO achieves state-of-the-art (SOTA) performance among reinforcement learning methods across all evaluation metrics.</p>"},{"id":"62164","en":"DSENet: A Novel Dual-Stream Enhancement Network for Multi-Scale Non-Stationary Time Series Forecasting","ko":"DSENet: 멀티스케일 비정상 시계열 예측용 Novel Dual-Stream Enhancement Network","authors":"Yuhan Wang, Yuanyuan Zou, Jie Cheng, Bin Dai, Jinhong Guo","pos":"#606","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=jAJJfsEwtd","abs":"<p>Accurately capturing local variations in long series has always been  one of the most challenging problems in time-series forecasting especially in medical signals, where local variations often indicate pathological events. Our study reveals a previously overlooked key bottleneck in this field: traditional global and local branches learn similar representations, leading to strong feature coupling and reduced sensitivity to local variations. To address this challenge, we propose the novel Dual-Stream Enhancement Mechanism, which structurally enlarges the difference between global and local patterns, enabling weak interactions between the two. Based on this idea, we introduce a new baseline model for blood glucose prediction: Dual-Stream Enhancement Network (DSENet), which fundamentally alleviates the problem of excessively strong coupling between global and local features. Experimental results show that our model achieves SOTA performance on multiple public datasets. Moreover, benefiting from extremely low computational cost, our model demonstrates strong application potential and can serve as a baseline model in multiple domains in the future.</p>","absKo":"<p>긴 시계열에서의 local variation을 정확히 포착하는 일은 시계열 forecasting에서 늘 가장 어려운 문제 중 하나였으며, 특히 local variation이 병리적 사건을 의미하는 medical signal에서는 더욱 그러하다. 우리의 연구는 이 분야에서 이전에 간과되었던 핵심 병목을 밝혀낸다. 전통적인 global branch와 local branch가 유사한 representation을 학습하여, 강한 feature coupling과 local variation에 대한 낮은 민감도를 초래한다는 점이다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 global pattern과 local pattern 간 차이를 구조적으로 확대하여 두 branch 간의 상호작용을 약하게 만드는 새로운 Dual-Stream Enhancement Mechanism을 제안한다. 이 아이디어를 바탕으로 blood glucose prediction을 위한 새로운 baseline model인 Dual-Stream Enhancement Network(DSENet)를 제안하며, 이는 global feature와 local feature 사이의 과도하게 강한 coupling 문제를 근본적으로 완화한다. 실험 결과는 우리의 model이 여러 public dataset에서 SOTA 성능을 달성함을 보여준다. 또한 매우 낮은 computational cost의 이점을 바탕으로, 우리의 model은 강한 실용적 잠재력을 보이며 향후 여러 domain에서 baseline model로 활용될 수 있다.</p>"},{"id":"62853","en":"Structured Multi-modal Graph Disentanglement for Psychiatric Diagnosis","ko":"정신과 진단을 위한 구조화된 다중 모달 그래프 disentanglement","authors":"Hongyu Shi, Kaizhong Zheng, WS Zhai, Shuai Jiang, Liangjun Chen, Badong Chen","pos":"#3017","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=cX3r7kAqr1","abs":"<p>Multi-modal neuroimaging diagnosis must integrate cross-modal agreement with modality-specific complementarity, yet in real multi-site cohorts these signals are frequently entangled with site- and cohort-dependent correlations, yielding shortcut-driven predictions, fragile transfer, and limited interpretability. We propose Structured Multi-modal Graph Disentanglement (SMGD), which explicitly factorizes multi-modal graph representations into four components with distinct roles: shared diagnostic evidence, complementary diagnostic evidence, incidental cross-modal agreement, and modality-specific non-robust correlations. SMGD is realized as geometry-driven structure learning: under a mild distributional assumption, we develop mini-batch estimable surrogate regularizers that shape subspace organization and cross-modal relations, enforcing semantic consistency through relational geometry rather than centroid coincidence while suppressing confounded dependencies. Experiments on large multi-site datasets (ABIDE-I, SRPBS) show improved in-domain diagnosis and more reliable cross-dataset generalization under modality gap, without expert-crafted features. Code is available at: \\url{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/anonymous<em>ICML</em>2026/README.md}.</p>","absKo":"<p>멀티모달 neuroimaging 진단은 교차 모달 간 일치성과 modality-specific 보완성을 함께 통합해야 하지만, 실제 multi-site 코호트에서는 이러한 신호가 site 및 cohort에 의존하는 상관관계와 자주 얽혀 shortcut에 의존한 예측, 취약한 transfer, 제한적인 해석 가능성을 초래한다. 우리는 Structured Multi-modal Graph Disentanglement(SMGD)를 제안하며, 이는 멀티모달 graph representation을 서로 다른 역할을 갖는 네 가지 구성요소로 명시적으로 factorize한다: shared diagnostic evidence, complementary diagnostic evidence, incidental cross-modal agreement, 그리고 modality-specific non-robust correlations. SMGD는 geometry-driven structure learning으로 구현된다. 약한 distributional assumption 하에서, subspace organization과 cross-modal relation을 형성하는 mini-batch로 추정 가능한 surrogate regularizer를 개발하여, centroid의 일치가 아니라 relational geometry를 통해 semantic consistency를 강제하고 confounded dependency를 억제한다. 대규모 multi-site 데이터셋(ABIDE-I, SRPBS) 실험에서 expert-crafted feature 없이도 in-domain 진단 성능이 향상되고 modality gap 하에서 cross-dataset generalization이 더 신뢰성 있게 개선됨을 보였다. 코드는 다음에서 제공된다: \\url{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/anonymous<em>ICML</em>2026/README.md}</p>"},{"id":"67163","en":"Position: Genomic Model Research Must Move Beyond Anecdotal Evaluation of Interpretability Methods","ko":"Position: Genomic 모델 연구는 해석 가능성 방법에 대한 일화적 평가를 넘어서야 한다","authors":"Shasha Zhou, Mingyu Huang, Ke Li","pos":"#3311","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Orp9hTiNEY","abs":"<p>Advances in machine learning and computational power have unlocked the predictive potential of the human genome, yet biologists increasingly demand that these models also elucidate the underlying biological mechanisms. While interpretable machine learning (IML) techniques have been increasingly applied to bridge this gap, there has been a pervasive reliance on anecdotal validation: the vast majority of research employs a single IML method and reports only isolated successful instances. Through a benchmarking study on transcription factor binding, we demonstrate the risks of current practices. We show that different IML methods can often (1) yield contradictory explanations for identical predictions, (2) fail to localize known regulatory motifs, and (3) do not faithfully reflect the model's internal decision process. In light of this, we argue for a validation framework analogous to clinical trials. Just as trials require rigorous design and the reporting of adverse events, genomic interpretability must move beyond cherry-picked plausibility toward systematic assessment of consistency, faithfulness, and biological validity. To facilitate this, we propose a tiered framework to guide the rigorous evaluation and reporting of genomic IML methods.</p>"},{"id":"65829","en":"Learning Treatment Allocations with Risk Control Under Partial Identifiability","ko":"부분 식별 가능성 하에서 위험 제어를 갖춘 처치 할당 학습","authors":"Sofia Ek, Dave Zachariah","pos":"#4411","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=9kWVQtpvJi","abs":"<p>Learning beneficial treatment allocations for a patient population is an important problem in precision medicine. For such allocations, a certain proportion of treated patients may not receive any benefit. This proportion of unnecessary treated represents a `treatment risk' which is a waste of resources and may, in addition, expose patients to unnecessary adverse effects. Therefore, we aim to  control the treatment risk when learning beneficial allocations. This  learning problem is complicated by the fact that the treatment risk is generally not identifiable from either randomized trial or observational data. We propose a certifiable learning method that controls treatment risk, using finite samples in the partially identified setting. The method is illustrated using both simulated and real data.</p>"},{"id":"61602","en":"TwinWeaver: An LLM-Based Foundation Model Framework for Pan-Cancer Digital Twins","ko":"TwinWeaver: Pan-Cancer Digital Twins를 위한 LLM 기반 Foundation Model Framework","authors":"Nikita Makarov, Maria Bordukova, Lena von Voithenberg, Estrella Pivel-Villanueva, Sabrina Mielke, Jonathan Wickes, Hanchen Wang, Mingyu Ma, Keunwoo Choi, Kyunghyun Cho, Stephen Ra, Raul Rodriguez-Esteban, Fabian Schmich, Michael Menden","pos":"#505","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=oWqRhYpJb6","abs":"Precision oncology requires forecasting clinical events and trajectories, yet modeling sparse, multi-modal clinical time series remains a critical challenge. We introduce TwinWeaver, an open-source framework that serializes longitudinal patient histories into text, enabling unified event prediction as well as forecasting with large language models, and use it to build Genie Digital Twin (GDT) on 93,054 patients across 20 cancer types. In benchmarks, GDT significantly reduces forecasting errors, achieving a median Mean Absolute Scaled Error (MASE) of 0.87 compared to 0.97 for the strongest time-series baseline ($p&lt;0.001$). Furthermore, GDT improves risk stratification, achieving an average concordance index (C-index) of 0.703 across survival, progression, and therapy switching tasks, surpassing the best baseline of 0.662. GDT also generalizes to out-of-distribution clinical trials, matching trained baselines at zero-shot and surpassing them with fine-tuning, achieving a median MASE of 0.75–0.88 and outperforming the strongest baseline in event prediction with an average C-index of 0.672 versus 0.648. Finally, TwinWeaver enables an interpretable clinical reasoning extension, providing a scalable and transparent foundation for longitudinal clinical modeling.","absKo":"정밀 종양학에서는 임상 사건과 궤적을 예측해야 하지만, 희소하고 multi-modal인 임상 시계열을 모델링하는 것은 여전히 핵심 과제다. 우리는 장기적 환자 이력을 텍스트로 직렬화하여 LLM으로 통합된 사건 예측과 forecasting을 가능하게 하는 오픈소스 프레임워크 TwinWeaver를 소개하고, 이를 사용해 20개 암 유형에 걸친 93,054명의 환자 데이터로 Genie Digital Twin (GDT)을 구축했다. 벤치마크에서 GDT는 예측 오차를 유의하게 줄여, 가장 강력한 시계열 baseline의 0.97과 비교해 median Mean Absolute Scaled Error (MASE) 0.87을 달성했다($p&lt;0.001$). 더 나아가 GDT는 생존, 진행, 치료 전환 task 전반에서 평균 concordance index (C-index) 0.703을 달성해, 최우수 baseline의 0.662를 능가하며 risk stratification을 개선한다. GDT는 또한 out-of-distribution 임상시험으로 일반화되어, zero-shot에서 학습된 baseline과 대등하고 fine-tuning으로 이를 넘어서는 성능을 보이며, median MASE 0.75–0.88을 달성하고 사건 예측에서는 평균 C-index 0.672로 최강 baseline의 0.648을 상회한다. 마지막으로 TwinWeaver는 해석 가능한 임상 추론 확장을 가능하게 하여, 장기적 임상 모델링을 위한 확장 가능하고 투명한 기반을 제공한다."},{"id":"64612","en":"Thinking in Scales: Accelerating Gigapixel Pathology Image Analysis via  Adaptive Continuous Reasoning","ko":"스케일로 사고하기: 적응적 연속 추론을 통한 Gigapixel 병리 영상 분석 가속화","authors":"Jiusong Ge, Yingkang Zhan, Wenjie Zhao, Di Zhang, Ke Wang, Jiashuai Liu, Chunze Yang, Chengzu Li, Jian Zhang, Yuxin Dong, Ni Zhang, Qidong Liu, Mireia Crispin-Ortuzar, Huazhu Fu, Chen Li, Zeyu Gao","pos":"#506","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=LgFmen6sHP","abs":"<p>Traditional whole slide image (WSI) analysis methods typically rely on the multiple instance learning (MIL) paradigm, which extracts patch-level features at high magnification and aggregates them for slide-level prediction.  However, such exhaustive patch-level processing is computationally expensive, severely limiting the efficiency and scalability of WSI analysis.  To address this challenge,  we propose \\textbf{PathCTM} (a \\textbf{\\ul{Path}}ology-oriented \\textbf{\\ul{C}}ontinuous \\textbf{\\ul{T}}hought \\textbf{\\ul{M}}odel) that enables token-efficient scale-space continuous reasoning for gigapixel WSIs. PathCTM formulates diagnostic inference as a dynamic sequential information pursuit. It progressively transitions from low-magnification global to high-magnification local inspection, and adaptively terminates inference when sufficient evidence is gathered to effectively bound decision uncertainty.  Specifically, it uses conditional computation for dynamic scale switching with attention-guided region pruning, coupled with confidence-aware early stopping. Extensive experiments demonstrate that compared with state-of-the-art MIL methods, PathCTM reduces the number of required image patches by 95.95\\%, shortens inference time by approximately 95.62\\%, and improves AUC by an average of 2.3\\%. Code is available at \\url{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/PathCTM}.</p>","absKo":"<p>전통적인 whole slide image (WSI) 분석 방법은 일반적으로 multiple instance learning (MIL) 패러다임에 의존하며, 이는 고배율에서 patch-level feature를 추출해 slide-level prediction을 위해 이를 집계한다. 그러나 이러한 전수적인 patch-level 처리는 계산 비용이 매우 커서 WSI 분석의 효율성과 확장성을 심각하게 제한한다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 기가픽셀 WSI를 위한 token-efficient scale-space continuous reasoning을 가능하게 하는 \\textbf{PathCTM} (\\textbf{\\ul{Path}}ology-oriented \\textbf{\\ul{C}}ontinuous \\textbf{\\ul{T}}hought \\textbf{\\ul{M}}odel)을 제안한다. PathCTM은 진단 추론을 동적인 순차적 정보 탐색으로 정식화한다. 이는 저배율의 전역적 관찰에서 고배율의 국소적 검사로 점진적으로 전환하며, 충분한 근거가 수집되어 의사결정 불확실성을 효과적으로 상한할 수 있을 때 추론을 적응적으로 종료한다. 구체적으로, attention-guided region pruning과 결합된 동적 scale switching을 위한 conditional computation과 confidence-aware early stopping을 사용한다. 광범위한 실험은 state-of-the-art MIL 방법들과 비교했을 때 PathCTM이 필요한 image patch 수를 95.95\\% 줄이고, 추론 시간을 약 95.62\\% 단축하며, AUC를 평균 2.3\\% 향상시킴을 보여준다. 코드는 \\url{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/PathCTM}에서 제공된다.</p>"},{"id":"63858","en":"The Double Dilemma in Multi-Task Radiology Report Generation: A Gradient Dynamics Analysis and Solution","ko":"멀티태스크 방사선 판독문 생성의 이중 딜레마: 그래디언트 동역학 분석과 해결","authors":"Erjian Zhang, Yatong Hao, Liejun Wang, Zhiqing Guo","pos":"#507","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=T7y2wavrFM","abs":"<p>While multi-task learning based automatic radiology report generation (RRG) is widely adopted to ensure clinical consistency, most focus on architectural designs yet remain limited to coarse linear scalarization strategies. These strategies can not effectively balance the hard constraints of discriminative clinical supervision with the smoothness requirements of report generation. To address these problems, we analyze the failure mechanism of linear scalarization from the perspective of gradient dynamics for the first time, utilizing the stochastic differential equation (SDE) framework to formalize it as a \"Double Dilemma'' of drift term deviation and diffusion term decay. Based on this, we propose a backbone-agnostic optimizer named Conflict-Averse Magnitude-Enhanced Gradient Descent (CAME-Grad). Through conflict-averse direction rectification and magnitude-enhanced energy injection, the algorithm not only ensures geometric validity, but also avoids the local optimal solution. Then, the adaptive gradient fusion technology is used to establish a dynamic balance between the theoretical optimal direction and the task-specific inductive bias. Experiments show that as a universal plug-and-play optimizer, CAME-Grad brings substantial and consistent improvements across eight diverse RRG methods, elevating overall clinical efficacy performance by an average of 2.3% on MIMIC-CXR and 1.9% on IU X-Ray. Our code is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/CAME-Grad-04A7.</p>","absKo":"<p>multi-task learning 기반 automatic radiology report generation(RRG)은 clinical consistency를 보장하기 위해 널리 채택되고 있지만, 대부분의 연구는 architectural design에 초점을 맞추는 반면 coarse한 linear scalarization strategy에만 머물러 있다. 이러한 전략은 discriminative clinical supervision의 hard constraint와 report generation의 smoothness requirement 사이의 균형을 효과적으로 맞추지 못한다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 gradient dynamics 관점에서 linear scalarization의 실패 메커니즘을 처음으로 분석하고, stochastic differential equation(SDE) framework를 활용하여 drift term deviation과 diffusion term decay의 \"Double Dilemma\"로 이를 정식화한다. 이를 바탕으로 우리는 Conflict-Averse Magnitude-Enhanced Gradient Descent(CAME-Grad)라는 backbone-agnostic optimizer를 제안한다. conflict-averse direction rectification과 magnitude-enhanced energy injection을 통해, 이 알고리즘은 geometric validity를 보장할 뿐 아니라 local optimal solution도 회피한다. 이어서 adaptive gradient fusion technology를 사용해 이론적 optimal direction과 task-specific inductive bias 사이의 동적 균형을 확립한다. 실험 결과, 범용 plug-and-play optimizer로서 CAME-Grad는 8개의 다양한 RRG method 전반에서 substantial하고 일관된 향상을 가져오며, MIMIC-CXR에서는 overall clinical efficacy performance를 평균 2.3%, IU X-Ray에서는 1.9% 향상시킨다. 코드는 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/CAME-Grad-04A7 에서 확인할 수 있다.</p>"},{"id":"64732","en":"Salus: Strategic Diagnostic Testing for Complex Diagnosis via Multi-Agent Reinforcement Learning","ko":"Salus: Multi-Agent Reinforcement Learning을 통한 복잡한 진단을 위한 전략적 진단 검사","authors":"Shuohao Gao, Xuanzhong Chen, Lingxiao Luo, Zilin Ding, Rong Han, Rui Jiang, Ting Chen","pos":"#509","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=KPsrOYaU79","abs":"Diagnosing complex diseases is inherently a sequential and iterative medical investigation process, in which a clinician strategically requests multiple rounds of diagnostic tests to differentiate among similar diseases until reaching a definitive diagnosis.  Although large language models show great potential as clinical assistants, they often struggle to navigate this complex interactive process, suffering from premature diagnostic closure. Furthermore, optimizing LLMs for such multi-round environments is frequently hindered by the challenge of reward sparsity and hacking. In this paper, we introduce $\\textbf{CompDiag-Bench}$, a benchmark that formalizes diagnosis as a sequential decision-making process where a clinician must strategically request diagnostic tests from a dynamic environment in order to reach a definitive diagnosis. To address this task, we propose $\\texttt{Salus}$, a multi-agent framework that decouples diagnostic reasoning into three specialized functional roles: a Differential Reasoner, a Strategic Controller, and a Workup Proposer.  $\\texttt{Salus}$ is optimized via multi-agent reinforcement learning employing structured rewards to calibrate strategic diagnostic behavior. Specifically, we leverage an LLM-as-a-Judge reward mechanism to provide dense, semantically-grounded feedback, designed to penalize premature closure and incentivize accurate differential diagnoses.  Experimental results show that our model, $\\texttt{Salus-7B}$, attains state-of-the-art Top-1 accuracy of $83.64\\%$ on complex cases, outperforming DeepSeek-V3.2 ($71.38\\%$) and achieving performance on par with GPT-5.2 ($80.30\\%$).","absKo":"복잡한 질병의 진단은 본질적으로 순차적이고 반복적인 의료 조사 과정으로, 임상의는 최종 진단에 도달할 때까지 유사한 질병들을 구분하기 위해 여러 차례의 diagnostic test를 전략적으로 요청한다. 대규모 언어 모델(LLM)은 clinical assistant로서 큰 잠재력을 보이지만, 이러한 복잡한 상호작용 과정에서 종종 어려움을 겪으며 premature diagnostic closure에 빠지곤 한다. 더 나아가, 이러한 multi-round 환경에 맞게 LLM을 최적화하는 일은 reward sparsity와 hacking 문제 때문에 자주 저해된다. 본 논문에서는 진단을 순차적 의사결정 과정으로 정식화하고, 임상의가 동적인 환경에서 definitive diagnosis에 도달하기 위해 diagnostic test를 전략적으로 요청해야 하는 \\textbf{CompDiag-Bench}를 소개한다. 이 과제를 해결하기 위해 우리는 diagnostic reasoning을 세 가지 특화된 기능 역할로 분리하는 multi-agent framework인 \\texttt{Salus}를 제안한다: Differential Reasoner, Strategic Controller, Workup Proposer. \\texttt{Salus}는 strategic diagnostic behavior를 조정하기 위해 structured reward를 사용하는 multi-agent reinforcement learning으로 최적화된다. 구체적으로, 우리는 LLM-as-a-Judge reward mechanism을 활용해 촘촘하고 의미적으로 근거 있는 피드백을 제공하며, 이를 통해 premature closure를 억제하고 정확한 differential diagnosis를 장려하도록 설계했다. 실험 결과, 우리의 모델인 \\texttt{Salus-7B}는 complex case에서 83.64\\%의 state-of-the-art Top-1 accuracy를 달성했으며, DeepSeek-V3.2(71.38\\%)를 능가하고 GPT-5.2(80.30\\%)와 동등한 수준의 성능을 보였다."},{"id":"66138","en":"Regulating Anatomy-Aware Rewards via Trajectory-Integral Feedback for Volumetric Computed Tomography Analysis","ko":"체적 컴퓨터 단층촬영 분석을 위한 궤적 적분 피드백 기반 해부학 인지 보상 조절","authors":"Tianwei Lin, Zhongwei Qiu, Jie Cao, Jiang Liu, Wenjie Yan, Bo Zhang, Yu Zhong, Wenqiao Zhang, Yingda Xia, Ling Zhang","pos":"#510","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=6YVSHa3g4b","abs":"<p>The advancement of Medical Vision-Language Models (VLMs) for 3D Computed Tomography (CT) analysis is hindered by a misalignment between optimization objectives and clinical rigor. Current Reinforcement Learning (RL) paradigms rely on lexical proxy signals that induce <code>\\textbf{evaluation hallucinations}'', where models prioritize linguistic fluency over factual accuracy, leading to fatal clinical errors. To bridge this gap, we introduce the \\textbf{Clinical Abnormality Benchmarking Substrate (CABS)}, a structured system that decomposes radiology reports into verifiable semantic units. Using CABS, we identify a</code>\\textbf{mechanistic divergence}'' in standard RL, where surface-similarity rewards drive policy gradients to bypass medical facts. We therefore propose \\textbf{Trajectory-Integral Feedback GRPO (TIF-GRPO)}, a novel framework integrating control-theoretic principles into policy optimization. By formulating clinical reasoning as a pseudo-temporal trajectory for anomaly discovery, TIF-GRPO regulates anatomy-aware rewards via an integral feedback loop that penalizes persistent omissions as cumulative state errors and suppresses hallucinations as excessive control effort. Experiments on 3D CT benchmarks demonstrate that our approach significantly enhances abnormality detection and clinical faithfulness, establishing a new paradigm for fine-grained regulation in medical VLMs.</p>"},{"id":"66434","en":"Process Reward Agents for Steering Knowledge-Intensive Reasoning","ko":"지식 집약적 추론을 이끄는 Process Reward Agent","authors":"Jiwoong Sohn, Tomasz Sternal, Kenneth Styppa, Torsten Hoefler, Michael Moor","pos":"#511","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=3moDc5lpBC","abs":"<p>Reasoning in knowledge-intensive domains remains challenging because intermediate steps are often not locally verifiable: unlike math or code, evaluating step correctness may require synthesizing clues across large external knowledge sources. As a result, subtle errors can propagate through reasoning traces, potentially never to be detected. Prior work has proposed process reward models (PRMs), including retrieval-augmented variants. However, due to retrieval they operate post hoc by scoring completed trajectories which prevents their integration into dynamic inference procedures. Here, we introduce Process Reward Agents~(PRA), a test-time method for providing domain-grounded, online, step-wise rewards to a frozen reasoner. In contrast to prior retrieval-augmented PRMs, PRA enables search-based decoding to rank and prune candidate trajectories at every generation step. Experiments on multiple medical reasoning benchmarks demonstrate that PRA consistently outperforms strong baselines, achieving 80.9\\% accuracy on MedQA with Qwen3-4B, a new state of the art at the 4B scale. Crucially, PRA generalizes to unseen frozen policy models ranging from 0.5B to 8B parameters, improving their accuracy by up to +25.7\\% without any policy model updates. Ultimately, PRA suggests a paradigm in which frozen reasoners are decoupled from domain-specific tool-augmented reward modules, which enables the deployment of new backbones in complex domains without retraining. To support reproducibility, we release all code and data in an anonymous repository.</p>"},{"id":"67250","en":"Position: Medical AI Neglects Real Treatment Outcomes","ko":"Position: 의료 AI는 실제 치료 결과를 소홀히 한다","authors":"Shiva Kaul, Anjum Khurshid","pos":"#512","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=0e1KEGU9RD","abs":"<p>Medical AI has rapidly improved its ability to perform diagnostic and prognostic tasks that lead to treatment decisions. But understanding of treatment itself is still inadequately trained and evaluated, using human opinions and syntheses (especially texts such as biomedical publications and clinical practice guidelines) rather than actual underlying data on treatment outcomes. This neglect seriously limits the long-term potential of medical AI, and is already causing deficiencies in both frontier models and major benchmarks, as argued in this position paper. Real treatment outcomes, drawn from sources such as observational databases and randomized experiments, should be substantially incorporated into both training and evaluation. Improving these outcomes should be reemphasized as the goal of all medical AI.</p>"},{"id":"61641","en":"PathwayLLM: Explainable Clinical Trajectory Modeling with Structured Pathways for Sepsis Prediction","ko":"PathwayLLM: 패혈증 예측을 위한 구조화 Pathway 기반 설명 가능한 임상 궤적 모델링","authors":"Zhengqiu Yu, Yueping Ding, Xiangrong Liu","pos":"#513","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=oB7gZX7MKP","abs":"<p>Patient-level sepsis prediction in the ICU requires models that track how a patient’s condition evolves over time and integrate heterogeneous structured evidence from electronic health records. We present PathwayLLM, a trajectory-based framework that grounds prediction on temporal signals together with graph-structured and pathway-level clinical information derived from statistical dependency discovery. PathwayLLM follows a three-stage design. First, each observation window is encoded from multiple structured views, including physiological measurements, temporal dynamics, a heterogeneous patient–diagnosis–medication graph, and pathway signals constructed from discovered conditional independence structures among clinical variables. Second, these representations are provided to a pre-trained language model as auxiliary contextual embeddings so that risk prediction and evidence-conditioned text explanations can be learned jointly. Third, a Clinical Trajectory LSTM with Deterioration Attention aggregates window-level representations to highlight critical deterioration points and produce a patient-level risk score. On MIMIC-IV (15,410 ICU patients; 8.45% sepsis prevalence), PathwayLLM achieves AUROC 0.891 and AUPRC 0.724, outperforming strong time-series and pre-trained baselines. Ablation studies indicate that trajectory aggregation and structured clinical signals are key contributors, and clinician review suggests that the generated explanations are coherent, interpretable, and clinically relevant.</p>","absKo":"<p>ICU에서의 patient-level sepsis prediction은 patient의 상태가 시간에 따라 어떻게 변화하는지 추적하고 electronic health records에서 나온 heterogeneous structured evidence를 통합하는 model을 요구한다. 우리는 statistical dependency discovery로부터 도출된 temporal signal과 graph-structured 및 pathway-level clinical information에 prediction을 grounding하는 trajectory-based framework인 PathwayLLM을 제시한다. PathwayLLM은 3단계 설계를 따른다. 첫째, 각 observation window는 physiological measurement, temporal dynamics, heterogeneous patient–diagnosis–medication graph, 그리고 clinical variable 간 discovered conditional independence structure로부터 구성한 pathway signal을 포함한 여러 structured view로 인코딩된다. 둘째, 이러한 representation은 pre-trained language model에 auxiliary contextual embedding으로 제공되어 risk prediction과 evidence-conditioned text explanation을 jointly 학습할 수 있게 한다. 셋째, Deterioration Attention을 갖는 Clinical Trajectory LSTM이 window-level representation을 집계하여 중요한 악화 지점을 강조하고 patient-level risk score를 생성한다. MIMIC-IV(15,410 ICU patients; 8.45% sepsis prevalence)에서 PathwayLLM은 AUROC 0.891, AUPRC 0.724를 달성하여 강력한 time-series 및 pre-trained baseline을 능가한다. ablation study는 trajectory aggregation과 structured clinical signal이 핵심 기여 요소임을 보여주며, clinician review는 생성된 explanation이 coherent하고 interpretable하며 clinically relevant하다고 제안한다.</p>"},{"id":"64818","en":"PPI Candidate Ranking: Large-Scale Evaluation of a Domain Knowledge–Guided Pipeline","ko":"PPI 후보 순위화: Domain Knowledge-Guided 파이프라인의 대규모 평가","authors":"Maria Emilia Russo, Federico Di Valerio, Alessia Borghini, Alessio Ragno, Roberto Capobianco","pos":"#514","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=JRsQDPWFCC","abs":"<p>Computational approaches have become central to Protein–Protein Interaction (PPI) research, complementing experimental techniques that remain costly and incomplete. While modern deep learning methods capture diverse biological signals and hold promise in expanding the known interactome, empirical validation remains a critical bottleneck due to its long and expensive procedures. To address this challenge, we introduce the problem of PPI candidate ranking, aiming to prioritize interactions for experimental testing. We propose a novel framework that leverages domain knowledge through interpretability-guided ranking and further refines prioritization by integrating complementary sources of evidence, including interaction scores, structural plausibility, and biomedical language features. Evaluations on a large-scale dataset constructed from successive STRING releases demonstrate that our approach yields significant improvements over two state-of-the-art PPI prediction models, providing more accurate and biologically coherent rankings.</p>"},{"id":"60493","en":"Optimizing Inference-Time Compute for Medical Reasoning via Uncertainty Quantification","ko":"Uncertainty Quantification을 통한 의료 Reasoning의 Inference-Time Compute 최적화","authors":"Shaohao Rui, Kaitao Chen, Weijie Ma, Xiaosong Wang","pos":"#515","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=zlJehQJATy","abs":"Extended Chain-of-Thought (CoT) reasoning has significantly bolstered the capabilities of medical large language models (LLMs). However, current models exhibit static computational expenditure, applying lengthy reasoning processes indiscriminately to both simple queries and complex diagnostic cases. This inefficiency is particularly prohibitive in real-world healthcare, where clinical scenarios range from time-sensitive emergencies requiring rapid response to intricate pathologies demanding deep analysis. To address this, we propose **AdaThink-Med**, an end-to-end framework for adaptive reasoning via uncertainty-guided length calibration. Although the underlying mechanism is generalizable, we demonstrate its critical value in the medical domain, where balancing inference latency with diagnostic precision is paramount. AdaThink-Med leverages entropy-based uncertainty estimation within reinforcement fine-tuning to dynamically shape reward signals: it penalizes verbosity for high-confidence correct answers (e.g., straightforward knowledge retrieval) while incentivizing extended exploration for uncertain or ambiguous scenarios. Across six medical benchmarks, AdaThink-Med reduces inference token consumption by $4.7\\times$ to $6.4\\times$ on Qwen and Llama architectures, respectively, with minimal performance trade-offs. Notably, the model spontaneously develops distinct \"non-thinking'' and \"thinking'' modes, demonstrating an autonomous ability to allocate computational resources efficiently based on clinical urgency and complexity.","absKo":"Extended Chain-of-Thought (CoT) 추론은 medical large language models (LLMs)의 성능을 크게 향상시켰다. 그러나 현재 모델들은 정적인 연산 비용을 보이며, 단순한 질의와 복잡한 진단 사례 모두에 대해 길고 동일한 추론 과정을 무차별적으로 적용한다. 이러한 비효율성은 실제 의료 환경에서 특히 치명적이며, 임상 시나리오는 신속한 대응이 필요한 시간 민감 응급상황부터 깊은 분석이 요구되는 복잡한 병리까지 다양하게 존재한다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 불확실성 유도 길이 보정을 통한 적응형 추론을 위한 end-to-end 프레임워크인 **AdaThink-Med**를 제안한다. 그 기반 메커니즘은 일반화 가능하지만, 추론 지연과 진단 정밀도의 균형이 무엇보다 중요한 의료 도메인에서 그 핵심적 가치를 입증한다. AdaThink-Med는 reinforcement fine-tuning 내에서 entropy 기반 불확실성 추정을 활용해 보상 신호를 동적으로 형성한다. 즉, 확신도가 높고 정답인 응답(예: 단순한 지식 검색)에는 장황함을 벌하고, 불확실하거나 모호한 상황에는 더 긴 탐색을 장려한다. 여섯 개의 medical benchmark 전반에서 AdaThink-Med는 Qwen 및 Llama 아키텍처에서 각각 추론 토큰 소비를 $4.7\\times$에서 $6.4\\times$까지 줄이면서도 성능 저하는 최소화한다. 특히 이 모델은 별다른 명시적 지시 없이도 서로 다른 \"non-thinking'' 및 \"thinking'' 모드를 자발적으로 형성하며, 임상적 긴급성과 복잡도에 따라 연산 자원을 효율적으로 배분하는 자율적 능력을 보여준다."},{"id":"61491","en":"ORBIT: A Prognostic World Model for Ocular Reasoning Based on Imagined Trajectories","ko":"ORBIT: 상상된 Trajectory 기반 안구 추론을 위한 예후적 World Model","authors":"Jiangtao Yan, Huixun Jia, Yansheng Qiu, Yanlin Qu, Shujian Gao, Wei Yu, Zheng Wang, Diping Song, Xiaodong Sun","pos":"#516","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=pd6GY2x8FG","abs":"<p>The longitudinal management of blinding fundus diseases constitutes a Partially Observable Markov Decision Process (POMDP) necessitating a critical precision-risk trade-off between intervention and over-treatment, as true pathology is often obscured in static observations. However, existing paradigms fail to address this complexity. Traditional vision models remain uninterpretable and memoryless, and while Vision-Language Models (VLMs) excel in semantic understanding, they rely on unsafe open-loop text reasoning lacking the anatomical grounding essential for clinical safety. Furthermore, robust learning is hindered by the scarcity of process supervision in sparse clinical records.  To bridge this gap, we introduce the {Logic-Constrained Abductive Data Engine}. Operating on a ``Propose-and-Verify'' paradigm, it validates MLLM-Proposed biomarkers against clinical and temporal logic to reconstruct dense pathological states from sparse outcomes. Building on this foundation, we propose ORBIT, the first ophthalmic Prognostic World Model. Uniquely, ORBIT employs counterfactual visual foresight to imagine anatomical futures under different treatments, anchoring decisions in Closed-Loop Anatomical Verification rather than linguistic probabilities. Experiments demonstrate that ORBIT effectively captures disease evolution and establishes a new paradigm for autonomous diagnosis and reliable decision-making in complex ophthalmic environments.</p>","absKo":"<p>blinding fundus disease의 종적 관리는 부분 관측 마르코프 의사결정 과정(Partially Observable Markov Decision Process, POMDP)을 구성하며, 실제 병리가 정적인 관찰에서 종종 가려지기 때문에 개입과 과잉치료 사이의 중대한 정밀도-위험 trade-off를 필요로 한다. 그러나 기존 paradigms는 이러한 복잡성을 다루지 못한다. 전통적인 vision model은 여전히 해석 불가능하고 기억이 없으며, Vision-Language Model(VLM)은 의미 이해에는 뛰어나지만 임상 안전에 필수적인 해부학적 grounding이 부족한 unsafe open-loop text reasoning에 의존한다. 더 나아가, 희소한 임상 기록에서 process supervision이 부족해 robust learning이 저해된다. 이 간극을 메우기 위해 우리는 {Logic-Constrained Abductive Data Engine}을 제안한다. ``Propose-and-Verify'' paradigm에서 동작하는 이 엔진은 MLLM이 제안한 biomarker를 clinical 및 temporal logic에 대해 검증하여, 희소한 outcome으로부터 밀도 높은 pathological state를 재구성한다. 이 기반 위에서 우리는 최초의 ophthalmic Prognostic World Model인 ORBIT를 제안한다. ORBIT는 치료에 따른 해부학적 미래를 상상하는 counterfactual visual foresight를 독특하게 활용하여, linguistic probability가 아니라 Closed-Loop Anatomical Verification에 의사결정을 정박시킨다. 실험은 ORBIT가 질병의 진화를 효과적으로 포착하고, 복잡한 안과 환경에서 자율 진단과 신뢰할 수 있는 의사결정을 위한 새로운 paradigm을 확립함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"60990","en":"Agentic Framework for Epidemiological Modeling","ko":"역학 모델링을 위한 Agentic 프레임워크","authors":"Rituparna Datta, Zihan Guan, Baltazar Espinoza, Yiqi Su, Priya Pitre, Srini Venkatramanan, Naren Ramakrishnan, Anil Vullikanti","pos":"#600","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ujYdUdqWpm","abs":"<p>Epidemic modeling is essential for public health planning, yet traditional approaches rely on fixed model classes that require manual redesign as pathogens, policies, and scenario assumptions evolve. We introduce EpiAgent, an agentic framework that automatically synthesizes, calibrates, verifies, and refines epidemiological simulators by modeling disease progression as an iterative program synthesis problem. A central design choice is an explicit epidemiological flow graph intermediate representation that links scenario specifications to model structure and enables strong, modular correctness checks before code is generated. Verified flow graphs are then compiled into mechanistic models supporting interpretable parameter learning under physical and epidemiological constraints. Evaluation on epidemiological scenario case studies demonstrates that EpiAgent captures complex growth dynamics and produces epidemiologically consistent counterfactual projections across varying vaccination and immune escape assumptions. Our results show that the agentic feedback loop prevents degeneration and significantly accelerates convergence toward valid models by mimicking professional expert workflows.</p>","absKo":"<p>Epidemic modeling은 공중보건 계획에 필수적이지만, 전통적인 접근은 고정된 model class에 의존하므로 병원체, 정책, 시나리오 가정이 변화할 때마다 수동으로 재설계해야 한다. 우리는 질병 진행을 반복적 program synthesis 문제로 모델링하여 epidemiological simulator를 자동으로 합성, 보정, 검증, 정교화하는 agentic framework인 EpiAgent를 제안한다. 핵심 설계 선택은 시나리오 명세를 모델 구조에 연결하고 code가 생성되기 전에 강력하고 모듈화된 correctness check를 가능하게 하는 explicit epidemiological flow graph intermediate representation이다. 검증된 flow graph는 이후 physical 및 epidemiological constraint 하에서 해석 가능한 parameter learning을 지원하는 mechanistic model로 컴파일된다. epidemiological scenario case study에 대한 평가는 EpiAgent가 복잡한 성장 동역학을 포착하고, vaccination 및 immune escape 가정이 달라져도 epidemiologically consistent counterfactual projection을 생성함을 보여준다. 우리의 결과는 agentic feedback loop가 전문가의 실제 워크플로를 모방함으로써 degeneration을 방지하고 valid model로의 수렴을 크게 가속함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"64231","en":"Benchmarking the Scientific Mind: Toward Evaluation of Complex-Reasoning Biomedical VQA","ko":"과학적 사고 벤치마킹: 복잡 추론 생의학 VQA 평가를 향하여","authors":"Ziyu Zhao, Yiyang Liu, Yajiao Wang, Xiaotao Wang, Yang Li, Yuyang Peng, Jiaheng Zhou, Jinqiao Wang, Yingying Chen, Ge Yang, Haixin Wang","pos":"#601","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Pj1Z7dWm4v","abs":"<p>Despite progress of Multimodal Large Language Models (MLLMs) in biomedical visual question answering (VQA), existing benchmarks provide limited assessment of their scientific reasoning capabilities. Most datasets adopt single-image question construction and outcome-oriented evaluation, where correctness is judged by answer plausibility rather than alignment with experimental evidence. Such formulations fail to capture the evidence-constrained, multi-step nature of biomedical reasoning, and obscure whether models can derive conclusions through causal interpretation of experimental observations.   To address these critical gaps in reasoning evaluation, we propose a principled benchmark construction framework that reconstructs scientific reasoning paths directly from biomedical literature. By jointly modeling clusters of experimentally related images together with their captions and context, the framework generates tightly coupled question–reasoning–answer triples that require multi-image integration and explicit evidence-driven inference. Based on this framework, we introduce \\textbf{SORBE} (\\textbf{S}cientific \\textbf{O}bservation &amp;amp; \\textbf{R}easoning for \\textbf{B}iomedical \\textbf{E}valuation), a large-scale multi-image biomedical VQA benchmark designed to evaluate evidence alignment and multi-step experimental reasoning. Under a process-oriented evaluation metric, state-of-the-art biomedical-specialized MLLMs exhibit substantial performance degradation, revealing systematic limitations in evidence grounding and causal reasoning that are not reflected by existing benchmarks.</p>","absKo":"<p>Biomedical visual question answering(VQA)에서 Multimodal Large Language Models(MLLMs)의 발전에도 불구하고, 기존 benchmark는 이들의 scientific reasoning 능력에 대한 평가가 제한적이다. 대부분의 dataset은 단일 이미지 question construction과 outcome-oriented evaluation을 채택하여, 정답 여부를 답변의 개연성으로 판단할 뿐 experimental evidence와의 정합성은 반영하지 않는다. 이러한 형식은 biomedical reasoning의 evidence-constrained, multi-step 특성을 포착하지 못하며, 모델이 실험 관찰의 causal interpretation을 통해 결론을 도출할 수 있는지 여부를 흐리게 만든다.   이러한 reasoning evaluation의 중대한 공백을 해결하기 위해, 우리는 biomedical literature로부터 scientific reasoning path를 직접 재구성하는 원칙적인 benchmark construction framework를 제안한다. 실험적으로 연관된 이미지 클러스터를 그 캡션 및 context와 함께 공동 모델링함으로써, 이 framework는 multi-image integration과 명시적인 evidence-driven inference를 요구하는 긴밀하게 결합된 question–reasoning–answer triple을 생성한다. 이 framework를 바탕으로, 우리는 evidence alignment와 multi-step experimental reasoning을 평가하기 위해 설계된 대규모 multi-image biomedical VQA benchmark인 \\textbf{SORBE}(\\textbf{S}cientific \\textbf{O}bservation &amp;amp; \\textbf{R}easoning for \\textbf{B}iomedical \\textbf{E}valuation)를 소개한다. process-oriented evaluation metric 하에서, 최신 biomedical-specialized MLLMs는 큰 성능 저하를 보이며, 이는 기존 benchmark에서는 드러나지 않던 evidence grounding과 causal reasoning의 체계적 한계를 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"61332","en":"Beyond Accuracy: Latent Perturbations for Cognitive-Aware Diagnosis","ko":"정확도를 넘어: 인지 인식 진단을 위한 잠재 교란","authors":"Yuting Yan, Yinghao Fu, Wendi Ren, Haozhou Gao, Shuang Li","pos":"#602","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=rEzGzILnVC","abs":"<p>Diagnosing rare diseases remains a persistent challenge, often hindered by <em>cognitive anchoring</em>:  once clinicians settle on a common diagnosis, they often discount alternative explanations, including rare conditions. To address this, we propose a human-centered counterfactual reasoning framework using a Denoising Masked AutoEncoder (DMAE) to simulate <em>what-if</em> diagnostic scenarios that disrupt clinicians’ initial assumptions. Our model jointly learns (1) the true distribution of diseases and symptoms, and (2) human diagnostic behavior, revealing critical gaps between <em>medically possible</em> and <em>clinically considered</em> diagnoses. By strategically perturbing latent patient representations, it generates <em>contrastive counterfactuals</em> that highlight rare yet plausible diseases that cognitive bias often obscures. Unlike traditional decision-support tools, our system <em>proactively</em> suggests rare diseases not because they are statistically probable, but because they are <em>cognitively neglected</em>. Across four public and three private rare-disease datasets, our approach outperforms standard machine learning classifiers in detecting rare conditions while maintaining strong performance on common diagnoses. Beyond boosting accuracy, the counterfactual evidence encourages <em>hypothesis-driven reasoning</em> and supports clinical learning.</p>","absKo":"<p>희귀 질환 진단은 지속적인 난제이며, 이는 종종 <em>cognitive anchoring</em>에 의해 방해를 받는다. 즉, 임상의가 흔한 진단에 한 번 안착하면 희귀 질환을 포함한 대안적 설명을 쉽게 배제하게 된다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 Denoising Masked AutoEncoder (DMAE)를 사용하여 임상의의 초기 가정을 흔드는 <em>what-if</em> 진단 시나리오를 시뮬레이션하는 인간 중심 반사실적 추론 프레임워크를 제안한다. 우리의 모델은 (1) 질병과 증상의 실제 분포, 그리고 (2) 인간의 진단 행동을 공동으로 학습하여, <em>medically possible</em>한 진단과 <em>clinically considered</em>된 진단 사이의 중요한 간극을 드러낸다. 잠재적 환자 표현을 전략적으로 교란함으로써, 인지 편향이 자주 가리는 희귀하지만 타당한 질환을 강조하는 <em>contrastive counterfactuals</em>를 생성한다. 전통적인 의사결정 지원 도구와 달리, 우리의 시스템은 희귀 질환이 통계적으로 더 유력해서가 아니라 <em>cognitively neglected</em>되어 있기 때문에 이를 <em>proactively</em> 제안한다. 네 개의 공개 데이터셋과 세 개의 비공개 희귀 질환 데이터셋 전반에서, 우리의 접근법은 흔한 진단에 대해서는 강력한 성능을 유지하면서도 희귀 질환 검출에서는 표준 machine learning 분류기를 능가한다. 정확도 향상을 넘어, 이러한 반사실적 증거는 <em>hypothesis-driven reasoning</em>을 촉진하고 임상 학습을 지원한다.</p>"},{"id":"63572","en":"Beyond Instance-Level Self-Supervision in 3D Multi-Modal Medical Imaging","ko":"3D 멀티모달 의료 영상에서 instance 수준 자기지도학습을 넘어","authors":"Tan Pan, Shuhao Mei, Yixuan Sun, Kaiyu Guo, Chen Jiang, Zhaorui Tan, Mengzhu Li, LIMEI HAN, Xiang Zou, Yuan Cheng, Mahsa Baktashmotlagh","pos":"#603","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Vtps0ZUlgv","abs":"<p>Self-supervised pre-training methods in medical imaging typically treat each individual as an isolated instance, learning representations through augmentation-based objectives or masked reconstruction. They often do not adequately capitalize on a key characteristic of physiological features: anatomical structures maintain consistent spatial relationships across individuals (instances), such as the thalamus being medial to the basal ganglia, regardless of variations in brain size, shape, or pathology. We propose leveraging this cross-instance topological consistency as a supervisory signal. The challenge arises from the inherent variability in medical imaging, which can differ significantly across instances and modalities. To tackle this, we focus on two alignment regimes. (i) Intra-instance: with pixel-level correspondences available, a cross-modal triplet objective explicitly preserves local neighborhood topology. (ii) Inter-instance: without such supervision, we derive pseudo-correspondences to control partial neighborhood alignment and prevent topology collapse across modalities. We validate our approach across 7 downstream multi-modal tasks, achieving average improvements of 1.1\\% and 5.94\\% in segmentation and classification tasks, respectively, and demonstrating significantly better robustness when modalities are missing at test time.</p>","absKo":"<p>medical imaging의 self-supervised pre-training 방법은 일반적으로 각 개인을 고립된 instance로 취급하고, augmentation 기반 objective 또는 masked reconstruction을 통해 representation을 학습한다. 이러한 방법은 physiological feature의 핵심 특성, 즉 anatomical structure가 brain size, shape, pathology의 변화와 무관하게 thalamus가 basal ganglia의 medial에 위치하는 것처럼 instance 간에 일관된 spatial relationship을 유지한다는 점을 충분히 활용하지 못하는 경우가 많다. 우리는 이러한 cross-instance topological consistency를 supervisory signal로 활용할 것을 제안한다. 여기서 과제는 medical imaging에 내재한 변동성으로 인해 instance와 modality 전반에서 차이가 매우 클 수 있다는 점이다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 두 가지 alignment regime에 주목한다. (i) intra-instance: pixel-level correspondence가 이용 가능할 때, cross-modal triplet objective가 local neighborhood topology를 명시적으로 보존한다. (ii) inter-instance: 이러한 supervision이 없을 때, pseudo-correspondence를 도출하여 partial neighborhood alignment를 제어하고 modality 간 topology collapse를 방지한다. 우리는 이 접근을 7개의 downstream multi-modal task에서 검증했으며, segmentation과 classification task에서 각각 평균 1.1\\%와 5.94\\%의 향상을 달성했고, test time에 modality가 누락되었을 때 훨씬 더 우수한 robustness를 보였다.</p>"},{"id":"62969","en":"CLINIC : Evaluating Multilingual Trustworthiness in Language Models for Healthcare","ko":"CLINIC: 의료용 Language Models의 다국어 Trustworthiness 평가","authors":"Akash Ghosh, Srivarshinee Sridhar, Raghav Ravi, Muhsin Muhsin, Sriparna Saha, Chirag Agarwal","pos":"#604","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=bMsBArF8MT","abs":"<p>Integrating language models (LMs) in healthcare systems holds great promise for improving medical workflows and decision-making. However, a critical barrier to their real-world adoption is the lack of reliable evaluation of their trustworthiness, especially in multilingual healthcare settings. Existing LMs are predominantly trained in high-resource languages, making them ill-equipped to handle the complexity and diversity of healthcare queries in mid- and low-resource languages, posing significant challenges for deploying them in global healthcare contexts where linguistic diversity is key. In this work, we present \\textsc{Clinic}, a \\textbf{C}omprehensive Mu\\textbf{l}tilingual Benchmark to evaluate the trustworth\\textbf{i}ness of la\\textbf{n}guage models \\textbf{i}n health\\textbf{c}are. \\name systematically benchmarks LMs across five key dimensions of trustworthiness: truthfulness, fairness, safety, robustness, and privacy, operationalized through 18 diverse tasks, spanning 15 languages (covering all the major continents), and encompassing a wide array of critical healthcare topics like disease conditions, preventive actions, diagnostic tests, treatments, surgeries, and medications. Our extensive evaluation reveals that LMs struggle with factual correctness, demonstrate bias across demographic and linguistic groups, and are susceptible to privacy breaches and adversarial attacks. By highlighting these shortcomings, \\name lays the foundation for enhancing the global reach and safety of LMs in healthcare across diverse languages.</p>","absKo":"<p>의료 시스템에 language model (LM)을 통합하는 것은 의료 workflow와 의사결정을 개선하는 데 큰 가능성을 지닌다. 그러나 실제 적용을 가로막는 중요한 장벽은 특히 다국어 의료 환경에서 이들의 trustworthiness를 신뢰할 수 있게 평가할 수 없다는 점이다. 기존 LM은 주로 고자원 언어로 학습되어 있어, 중간 및 저자원 언어에서의 의료 질의가 지닌 복잡성과 다양성을 다루기에 부적합하며, 언어적 다양성이 핵심인 전 지구적 의료 환경에 배포할 때 큰 어려움을 초래한다. 이 연구에서는 의료에서 language model의 trustworthiness를 평가하기 위한 포괄적 다국어 benchmark인 \\textsc{Clinic}을 제시한다. \\name은 truthfulness, fairness, safety, robustness, privacy라는 trustworthiness의 다섯 핵심 차원을 따라 LM을 체계적으로 평가하며, 15개 언어(모든 주요 대륙을 포괄함)에 걸쳐 18개의 다양한 task로 이를 구체화하고, 질병 상태, 예방 조치, 진단 검사, 치료, 수술, 약물 등 광범위한 핵심 의료 주제를 포함한다. 광범위한 평가를 통해 LM이 사실적 정확성에서 어려움을 겪고, 인구통계학적 및 언어 집단 간 편향을 보이며, privacy 침해와 adversarial attack에 취약하다는 사실을 확인했다. 이러한 한계를 부각함으로써 \\name은 다양한 언어에 걸쳐 의료 분야에서 LM의 전 세계적 도달 범위와 안전성을 향상시키기 위한 기반을 마련한다.</p>"},{"id":"66715","en":"ClinTutor-R1: Advancing Scalable and Robust One-to-Many Alignment in Clinical Socratic Education","ko":"ClinTutor-R1: 임상 Socratic 교육에서 확장 가능하고 강건한 One-to-Many 정렬 발전","authors":"Zhitao He, Haolin Yang, Zeyu Qin, Yi Fung","pos":"#605","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=15Gs65kvHS","abs":"<p>While Large Language Models (LLMs) have achieved remarkable success in dyadic (one-on-one) instruction, they face significant challenges in One-to-Many alignment, such as clinical ward rounds, where an instructor must simultaneously guide a diverse group of trainees. Current models often suffer from context dilution and goal misalignment, failing to balance individual scaffolding with collective learning progress. To address this, we introduce ClinEdu, a multi-agent pedagogical simulator that model the complexity of group dynamics. Leveraging this platform, we construct ClinTeach, a large-scale dataset of Socratic teaching dialogues, and propose ClinTutor-R1, the first multimodal agent explicitly architected to achieve one-to-many alignment in clinical education, employing an explicit internal thinking mechanism to model both individual belief states and group consensus. We validate our framework through a comprehensive protocol covering both standard static benchmarks and rigorous in-situ interactive evaluation within ClinEdu. Experimental results demonstrate that ClinTutor-R1 outperforms base models by over 20% and achieves parity with proprietary reasoning models , while exhibiting exceptional scalability in maintaining instructional quality across expanding student cohorts.</p>"},{"id":"63264","en":"Dynamic Decision Learning: Test-Time Evolution for Abnormality Grounding in Rare Diseases","ko":"동적 결정 학습: 희귀 질환에서 이상 그라운딩을 위한 테스트타임 진화","authors":"Jun Li, Mingxuan Liu, Jiazhen Pan, che liu, Wenjia Bai, Cosmin Bercea, Julia Schnabel","pos":"#607","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=YcccAbXbVK","abs":"<p>Clinical abnormality grounding for rare diseases is often hindered by data scarcity, rendering supervised fine-tuning infeasible and single-pass inference highly unstable. Thus, we propose Dynamic Decision Learning (DDL), a framework that enables frozen LVLMs to refine their decisions across language and visual spaces by optimizing instructions and consolidating predictions under visual perturbations, thereby improving localization quality and producing a consensus‑based reliability score that quantifies the model’s confidence. Results on brain‑imaging benchmarks, including a rare‑disease dataset with 281 pathology types across 3B-72B models, show that DDL improves mAP@75 by up to 105\\% on rare‑disease cases and surpasses adaptation baselines and supervised fine‑tuning. Moreover, we show that DDL yields stronger calibration between consensus‑based reliability scores and localization accuracy under severe distribution shifts and increasing task difficulty. The code will be open-sourced.</p>","absKo":"<p>희귀 질환에서의 clinical abnormality grounding은 data scarcity로 인해 자주 방해받으며, 이로 인해 supervised fine-tuning은 사실상 불가능하고 single-pass inference는 매우 불안정해진다. 따라서 우리는 Dynamic Decision Learning (DDL)을 제안한다. DDL은 frozen LVLMs가 language 및 visual space 전반에서 instruction을 최적화하고 visual perturbation 하에서 prediction을 통합함으로써 결정을 점진적으로 정제할 수 있게 하는 framework이며, 그 결과 localization quality를 향상시키고 model의 confidence를 정량화하는 consensus‑based reliability score를 생성한다. 3B-72B models에 걸쳐 281개 pathology type을 포함하는 rare-disease dataset을 포함한 brain-imaging benchmark에서의 결과는 DDL이 rare-disease 사례에서 mAP@75를 최대 105\\%까지 향상시키고, adaptation baselines 및 supervised fine-tuning을 능가함을 보여준다. 또한 DDL은 심한 distribution shift와 task difficulty 증가 하에서 consensus‑based reliability score와 localization accuracy 사이의 calibration을 더 강하게 만든다는 점도 보인다. 코드는 공개될 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"65269","en":"Evidential Reasoning Advances Interpretable Real-World Disease Screening","ko":"증거적 추론이 해석 가능한 실세계 질병 선별을 발전시킨다","authors":"Chenyu Lian, Hong-Yu Zhou, Jing Qin","pos":"#608","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=FCVPVqRLDJ","abs":"<p>Disease screening is critical for early detection and timely intervention in clinical practice. However, current screening models for medical images often suffer from limited interpretability and suboptimal performance, as they lack mechanisms to reference historical cases or provide transparent reasoning pathways. To address these challenges, we introduce EviScreen, an evidential reasoning framework for disease screening that leverages region-level evidence retrieved from knowledge banks of historical cases. The proposed EviScreen offers retrospection interpretability through regional evidence retrieved from dual knowledge banks. Based on the evidential mechanism, the subsequent evidence-aware reasoning module makes predictions using both the current case and evidence from historical cases, thereby enhancing disease screening performance. In addition, unlike conventional methods that rely on post-hoc saliency maps, EviScreen enables advanced localization interpretability through abnormality maps generated via contrastive retrieval. Our method achieves superior performance on our carefully established benchmarks for real-world disease screening, yielding notably higher specificity at clinical-level recall, which reduces both unnecessary follow-up examinations and the associated psychological burden on patients. Code will be publicly available and is currently provided in supplementary material.</p>"},{"id":"64700","en":"Exploring Accurate and Transparent Domain Adaptation in Predictive Healthcare via Concept-Grounded Orthogonal Inference","ko":"Concept-Grounded Orthogonal Inference를 통한 예측적 헬스케어에서의 정확하고 투명한 도메인 적응 탐구","authors":"Pengfei Hu, Chang Lu, Feifan Liu, Yue Ning","pos":"#609","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=KidQq3EaOe","abs":"<p>Deep learning models for clinical event prediction on electronic health records (EHR) often suffer performance degradation when deployed under different data distributions.  While domain adaptation (DA) methods can mitigate such shifts, its \"black-box\" nature prevents widespread adoption in clinical practice where transparency is essential for trust and safety. We propose ExtraCare to decompose patient representations into invariant and covariant components.  By supervising these two components and enforcing their orthogonality during training, our model preserves label information while exposing domain-specific variation at the same time for more accurate predictions than most feature alignment models. More importantly, it offers human-understandable explanations by mapping sparse latent dimensions to medical concepts and quantifying their contributions via targeted ablations. ExtraCare is evaluated on two real-world EHR datasets across multiple domain partition settings, demonstrating superior performance along with enhanced transparency, as evidenced by its accurate predictions and explanations from extensive case studies.</p>","absKo":"<p>전자건강기록(EHR)에서의 clinical event prediction을 위한 deep learning model은 서로 다른 data distribution 하에 배포될 때 성능 저하를 겪는 경우가 많다. domain adaptation (DA) method가 이러한 shift를 완화할 수 있지만, 그 'black-box' 특성은 신뢰와 안전이 중요한 임상 환경에서의 광범위한 채택을 가로막는다. 우리는 patient representation을 invariant component와 covariant component로 분해하는 ExtraCare를 제안한다. 이 두 component를 supervision하고 학습 중 orthogonality를 강제함으로써, 우리의 model은 label information을 보존하는 동시에 domain-specific variation을 드러내어 대부분의 feature alignment model보다 더 정확한 예측을 가능하게 한다. 더욱 중요한 점은, sparse latent dimension을 medical concept에 매핑하고 targeted ablation을 통해 각 기여도를 정량화함으로써 사람이 이해할 수 있는 설명을 제공한다는 것이다. ExtraCare는 여러 domain partition setting에서 두 개의 실제 EHR dataset으로 평가되었으며, 광범위한 case study에서 정확한 예측과 설명으로 입증되는 우수한 성능과 향상된 투명성을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"63862","en":"FACT: Fuzzy Alignment with Comorbidity Topology for Reliable Multi-Label Medical Image Diagnosis","ko":"FACT: 신뢰할 수 있는 다중 레이블 의료영상 진단을 위한 comorbidity topology 기반 fuzzy alignment","authors":"Yingyu Chen, Yongqiang Huang, Yang Qin, Ziyuan Yang, Lang Yuan, Maosong Ran, Yi Zhang","pos":"#610","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=T5u3haVBgi","abs":"<p>In clinical practice, patients often present with multiple co-occurring diseases, yet most existing Multi-Label-Diagnosis (MLD) methods treat diagnosis as a rigid discriminative partitioning task, implicitly assuming that overlapping pathologies are separable. This assumption is problematic in medical images, where identical or highly similar visual observations may simultaneously support multiple disease labels, and disease concepts are inherently correlated rather than independent. Enforcing hard decision boundaries under such overlap suppresses shared evidence, biases feature representations, and ultimately undermines model reliability. To address this limitation, we propose Fuzzy Alignment with Comorbidity Topology FACT, a novel paradigm that reformulates MLD as a fuzzy alignment problem between atomic visual evidence and disease semantic anchors. FACT is characterized by three key features: (1) modeling visual polysemy through shared and reusable atomic visual evidence; (2) encoding disease correlation via semantic anchors structured by comorbidity topology; and (3) employing a metric-based fuzzy membership function for non-discriminative visual-semantic alignment. Extensive experiments on three public clinical benchmarks demonstrate that FACT consistently improves diagnostic performance while delivering clinically plausible predictions. The code will be available upon the acceptance of this paper.</p>","absKo":"<p>임상 현장에서는 환자가 여러 동반 질환을 함께 보이는 경우가 흔하지만, 기존의 대부분 Multi-Label-Diagnosis(MLD) 방법은 진단을 rigid한 discriminative partitioning task로 다루며, 겹치는 pathology가 서로 분리 가능하다고 암묵적으로 가정한다. 이러한 가정은 의료 영상에서 문제가 되는데, 동일하거나 매우 유사한 시각 관찰이 여러 disease label을 동시에 지지할 수 있고, disease concept는 본질적으로 독립적이라기보다 상호 연관되어 있기 때문이다. 이러한 overlap 하에서 hard decision boundary를 강제하면 shared evidence가 억제되고 feature representation에 편향이 생기며, 결국 model reliability를 저해한다. 이 한계를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 MLD를 atomic visual evidence와 disease semantic anchor 사이의 fuzzy alignment problem으로 재정식화하는 새로운 패러다임인 Fuzzy Alignment with Comorbidity Topology FACT를 제안한다. FACT는 세 가지 핵심 특징을 가진다. (1) 공유 가능하고 재사용 가능한 atomic visual evidence를 통해 visual polysemy를 모델링한다. (2) comorbidity topology로 구조화된 semantic anchor를 통해 disease correlation을 인코딩한다. (3) 비-discriminative visual-semantic alignment를 위해 metric-based fuzzy membership function을 사용한다. 세 개의 공개 clinical benchmark에서의 광범위한 실험은 FACT가 clinically plausible prediction을 제공하면서 진단 성능을 일관되게 향상시킴을 보여준다. 코드는 본 논문의 채택 후 공개될 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"65140","en":"Federated Distillation for Whole Slide Image via Gaussian-Mixture Feature Alignment and Curriculum Integration","ko":"Gaussian-Mixture 특징 정렬과 커리큘럼 통합을 통한 Whole Slide Image 연합 증류","authors":"Luru Jing, Cong Cong, Yanyuan Chen, Yongzhi Cao","pos":"#611","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=GPyay3ZTrk","abs":"<p>Federated learning (FL) offers a promising framework for collaborative digital pathology by enabling model training across institutions. However, real-world deployments face heterogeneity arising from diverse multiple instance learning (MIL) architectures and heterogeneous feature extractors across institutions. We propose FedHD, a novel FL framework that performs local Gaussian-mixture feature alignment tailored for WSI analysis. Instead of exchanging model parameters, each client independently distills semantically rich synthetic feature representations aligned with the distribution of real WSIs. To preserve diagnostic diversity, FedHD adopts a one-to-one distillation strategy, generating a synthetic counterpart for each real slide to avoid over-compression. During federation, a curriculum-based integration strategy progressively incorporates cross-site synthetic features into local training once performance plateaus. Furthermore, an optional interpretation module reconstructs pseudo-patches from synthetic embeddings, enhancing transparency. FedHD is architecture-agnostic, privacy-preserving, and supports personalized yet collaborative training across diverse institutions. Experiments on TCGA-IDH, CAMELYON16, and CAMELYON17 show that FedHD consistently outperforms state-of-the-art federated and distillation baselines.</p>"},{"id":"63972","en":"From Conflict to Consensus: Boosting Medical Reasoning via Multi-Round Agentic RAG","ko":"갈등에서 합의로: Multi-Round Agentic RAG를 통한 의료 추론 향상","authors":"Wenhao Wu, Zhentao Tang, Yafu Li, Shixiong Kai, Mingxuan Yuan, Zhenhong Sun, Chunlin Chen, Zhi Wang","pos":"#612","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=S7lpdz7NAW","abs":"<p>Large Language Models (LLMs) exhibit high reasoning capacity in medical question-answering, but their tendency to produce hallucinations and outdated knowledge poses critical risks in healthcare fields. While Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) mitigates these issues, existing methods rely on noisy token-level signals and lack the multi-round refinement required for complex reasoning. In the paper, we propose <strong>MA-RAG</strong> (<strong>M</strong>ulti-Round <strong>A</strong>gentic RAG), a framework that facilitates test-time scaling for complex medical reasoning by iteratively evolving both external evidence and internal reasoning history within an agentic refinement loop. At each round, the agent transforms semantic <strong>conflict</strong> among candidate responses into actionable queries to retrieve external evidence, while optimizing history reasoning traces to mitigate long-context degradation. MA-RAG extends the <em>self-consistency</em> principle by leveraging the lack of consistency as a proactive signal for multi-round agentic reasoning and retrieval, and mirrors a <em>boosting</em> mechanism that iteratively minimizes the residual error toward a stable, high-fidelity medical <strong>consensus</strong>. Extensive evaluations across 7 medical Q&amp;amp;A benchmarks show that MA-RAG consistently surpasses competitive inference-time scaling and RAG baselines, delivering <strong>substantial +6.8 points</strong> on average accuracy over the backbone model.</p>","absKo":"Large Language Models (LLMs)는 medical question-answering에서 높은 reasoning 능력을 보이지만, hallucination을 생성하고 오래된 지식을 사용할 수 있다는 점은 의료 분야에서 중대한 위험을 초래한다. Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)은 이러한 문제를 완화하지만, 기존 방법은 noisy token-level signal에 의존하며 복잡한 reasoning에 필요한 multi-round refinement가 부족하다. 본 논문에서는 <strong>MA-RAG</strong> (<strong>M</strong>ulti-Round <strong>A</strong>gentic RAG)를 제안한다. 이는 agentic refinement loop 안에서 외부 evidence와 내부 reasoning history를 반복적으로 진화시켜 복잡한 medical reasoning을 위한 test-time scaling을 가능하게 하는 framework이다. 각 round에서 agent는 후보 응답들 사이의 semantic <strong>conflict</strong>를 외부 evidence를 retrieval하기 위한 실행 가능한 query로 변환하는 한편, long-context degradation을 완화하기 위해 history reasoning trace를 최적화한다. MA-RAG는 <em>self-consistency</em> 원리를 확장하여, 일관성의 부재를 multi-round agentic reasoning과 retrieval을 위한 능동적 신호로 활용하며, 또한 안정적이고 high-fidelity인 medical <strong>consensus</strong>를 향해 잔차 오차를 반복적으로 최소화하는 <em>boosting</em> 메커니즘을 닮아 있다. 7개의 medical Q&amp;amp;A benchmark에 대한 광범위한 평가는 MA-RAG가 경쟁력 있는 inference-time scaling과 RAG baseline을 일관되게 능가하며, backbone 모델 대비 평균 정확도에서 <strong>6.8 points</strong>의 실질적인 향상을 제공함을 보여 준다.</p>"},{"id":"60554","en":"InfiMed-ORBIT: Aligning LLMs on Open-Ended Complex Tasks via Rubric-Based Incremental Training","ko":"InfiMed-ORBIT: 루브릭 기반 점진적 학습으로 개방형 복합 과제에서 LLM 정렬","authors":"Pengkai Wang, Pengwei Liu, Qi Zuo, Zhijie Sang, Congkai Xie, Hongxia Yang","pos":"#614","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=z2vVeIscEd","abs":"<p>Reinforcement learning (RL) has powered many of the recent breakthroughs in large language models (LLMs), especially for tasks where rewards can be computed automatically, such as code generation. However, these methods deteriorate in open-ended domains like medical consultation, where feedback is inherently ambiguous, highly context-dependent, and cannot be reduced to a reliable scalar signal.  In such settings, RL must either rely on supervision-intensive reward models that often fail to generalize, or it falls into pathological behaviors such as reward hacking—an especially troubling risk for high-stakes medical dialogue. To address these limitations, we introduce ORBIT, an open-ended rubric-based incremental training framework for high-stakes medical dialogue. ORBIT integrates synthetic dialogue generation with dynamically constructed rubrics that serve as adaptive guides for incremental RL.  Instead of relying on external medical knowledge bases or handcrafted rule sets, ORBIT uses rubric-driven feedback to steer the learning process.  Its judge component can be instantiated with general-purpose instruction-following LLMs, removing the need for any task-specific fine-tuning. Applied to the Qwen3-4B-Instruct model, ORBIT raises the HealthBench-Hard score from 7.0 to 27.5 using only 2k training samples, achieving SOTA performance for models at this scale.  With larger rubric datasets, ORBIT-trained models further compete with the strongest open-source baselines on HealthBench-Hard.  Our analysis shows that rubric-guided RL consistently improves consultation quality across diverse medical scenarios.  We also apply such rubric generation and training pipeline to InfoBench, where ORBIT enhances instruction-following performance, highlighting the generality of rubric-based feedback.</p>","absKo":"<p>Reinforcement learning (RL)은 최근 대규모 언어 모델(LLM)의 여러 돌파구를 이끌어 왔으며, 특히 code generation처럼 reward를 자동으로 계산할 수 있는 task에서 두드러졌다. 그러나 이러한 방법은 의학 상담처럼 feedback이 본질적으로 모호하고, 문맥 의존적이며, 신뢰할 수 있는 scalar signal로 환원될 수 없는 open-ended domain에서는 성능이 저하된다. 이러한 환경에서 RL은 일반화에 실패하는 경우가 많은 supervision-intensive reward model에 의존해야 하거나, 혹은 reward hacking과 같은 병적 행태로 빠질 수 있는데, 이는 high-stakes medical dialogue에서 특히 우려되는 위험이다. 이러한 한계를 해결하기 위해 우리는 high-stakes medical dialogue를 위한 open-ended rubric-based incremental training framework인 ORBIT을 제안한다. ORBIT은 synthetic dialogue generation과 동적으로 구성된 rubric을 통합하여 incremental RL을 위한 adaptive guide로 활용한다. 외부 medical knowledge base나 수작업 rule set에 의존하는 대신, ORBIT은 rubric-driven feedback을 사용해 learning process를 조정한다. judge component는 범용 instruction-following LLM으로 구현할 수 있어 task-specific fine-tuning이 전혀 필요 없다. Qwen3-4B-Instruct 모델에 적용했을 때, ORBIT은 2k training sample만으로 HealthBench-Hard 점수를 7.0에서 27.5로 끌어올려, 이 규모의 모델들 중 SOTA 성능을 달성했다. 더 큰 rubric dataset을 사용하면 ORBIT으로 학습된 모델은 HealthBench-Hard에서 가장 강력한 open-source baseline과도 경쟁력을 보인다. 우리의 분석은 rubric-guided RL이 다양한 medical scenario에서 consultation quality를 일관되게 향상시킨다는 점을 보여준다. 또한 이러한 rubric generation 및 training pipeline을 InfoBench에도 적용하여, ORBIT이 instruction-following 성능을 향상시킴으로써 rubric-based feedback의 일반성을 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"64357","en":"MedScope: Incentivizing \"Think with Videos\" for Clinical Reasoning via Coarse-to-Fine Tool Calling","ko":"MedScope: 조밀-정밀 도구 호출을 통한 임상 추론을 위한 \"영상으로 사고하기\" 유도","authors":"Wenjie Li, Yujie Zhang, Haoran Sun, Xingqi He, Hongcheng Gao, Chenglong Ma, Ming Hu, Guankun Wang, Shiyi Yao, Renhao Yang, Hongliang Ren, Lei Wang, Junjun He, Yankai Jiang","pos":"#615","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=OOyPj8hdiM","abs":"<p>Long-form clinical videos are central to visual evidence-based decision-making, with growing importance for applications such as surgical robotics and related settings. However, current multimodal large language models typically process videos with passive sampling or weakly grounded inspection, which limits their ability to iteratively locate, verify, and justify predictions with temporally targeted evidence. To close this gap, we propose <strong>MedScope</strong>, a tool-using clinical video reasoning model that performs coarse-to-fine evidence seeking over long-form procedures. By interleaving intermediate reasoning with targeted tool calls and verification on retrieved observations, MedScope produces more accurate and trustworthy predictions that are explicitly grounded in temporally localized visual evidence. To address the lack of high-fidelity supervision, we build <strong>ClinVideoSuite</strong>, an evidence-centric, fine-grained clinical video suite. We then optimize <strong>MedScope</strong> with <strong>G</strong>rounding-<strong>A</strong>ware <strong>G</strong>roup <strong>R</strong>elative <strong>P</strong>olicy <strong>O</strong>ptimization (<strong>GA-GRPO</strong>), which directly reinforces tool use with grounding-aligned rewards and evidence-weighted advantages. On full and fine-grained video understanding benchmarks, <strong>MedScope</strong> achieves state-of-the-art performance in both in-domain and out-of-domain evaluations. Our approach illuminates a path toward medical AI agents that can genuinely “think with videos” through tool-integrated reasoning. We will release our code, models, and data.</p>","absKo":"<p>장문 clinical video는 시각적 evidence-based decision-making의 핵심이며, surgical robotics 및 관련 환경과 같은 응용에서 그 중요성이 커지고 있습니다. 그러나 현재의 multimodal large language model은 대체로 video를 passive sampling하거나 약하게 grounded된 inspection으로 처리하여, 시간적으로 표적화된 evidence를 바탕으로 예측을 반복적으로 찾아내고, 검증하며, 정당화하는 능력이 제한됩니다. 이 격차를 해소하기 위해, 우리는 장시간 procedure 전반에 걸쳐 coarse-to-fine evidence seeking을 수행하는 tool-using clinical video reasoning model인 <strong>MedScope</strong>를 제안합니다. 중간 reasoning과 표적화된 tool call, 그리고 검색된 observation에 대한 verification을 교차적으로 수행함으로써, MedScope는 시간적으로 국소화된 visual evidence에 명시적으로 grounded된 더 정확하고 신뢰할 수 있는 예측을 생성합니다. 고충실도 supervision의 부족을 해결하기 위해, 우리는 evidence-centric하고 fine-grained한 clinical video suite인 <strong>ClinVideoSuite</strong>를 구축합니다. 이어서 우리는 grounding-aligned reward와 evidence-weighted advantage로 tool use를 직접 강화하는 <strong>G</strong>rounding-<strong>A</strong>ware <strong>G</strong>roup <strong>R</strong>elative <strong>P</strong>olicy <strong>O</strong>ptimization(<strong>GA-GRPO</strong>)으로 <strong>MedScope</strong>를 최적화합니다. 전체 및 fine-grained video understanding benchmark에서 <strong>MedScope</strong>는 in-domain과 out-of-domain 평가 모두에서 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성합니다. 우리의 접근은 tool-integrated reasoning을 통해 의료 AI agent가 진정으로 “video와 함께 생각할” 수 있는 길을 제시합니다. 우리는 code, model, data를 공개할 예정입니다.</p>"},{"id":"65042","en":"Near-Optimal Dynamic Matching via Coarsening with Application to Heart Transplantation","ko":"Coarsening을 통한 준최적 Dynamic Matching과 심장 이식에의 응용","authors":"Itai Zilberstein, Ioannis Anagnostides, Zachary Sollie, Arman Kilic, Tuomas Sandholm","pos":"#616","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=HQTsYta4XX","abs":"<p>Online matching has been a mainstay in domains such as Internet advertising and organ allocation, but practical algorithms often lack strong theoretical guarantees. We take an important step toward addressing this by developing new online matching algorithms based on a coarsening approach. Although coarsening typically implies a loss of granularity, we show that, to the contrary, aggregating offline nodes into capacitated clusters can yield near-optimal theoretical guarantees. We apply our methodology to heart transplant allocation to develop theoretically grounded policies based on structural properties of historical data. Furthermore, in simulations based on real data, our policy closely matches the performance of the omniscient benchmark, achieving competitive ratio 0.91, drastically higher than the US status quo policy's 0.51. Our work bridges the gap between data-driven heuristics and pessimistic theoretical lower bounds.</p>"},{"id":"62589","en":"AgentScore: Autoformulation of Deployable Clinical Scoring Systems","ko":"AgentScore: 배포 가능한 임상 Scoring System의 Autoformulation","authors":"Silas Ruhrberg Estevez, Chris Chiu, Mihaela van der Schaar","pos":"#700","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=fFUI2PGaNG","abs":"Modern clinical practice relies on evidence-based guidelines implemented as compact scoring systems composed of a small number of interpretable decision rules. While machine-learning models achieve strong performance, many fail to translate into routine clinical use due to misalignment with workflow constraints such as memorability, auditability, and bedside execution. We argue that this gap arises not from insufficient predictive power, but from optimizing over model classes that are incompatible with guideline deployment. Deployable guidelines often take the form of unit-weighted  clinical checklists, formed by thresholding the sum of binary rules, but learning such scores requires searching an exponentially large discrete space of possible rule sets. We introduce $\\texttt{AgentScore}$, which performs semantically guided optimization in this space by using LLMs to propose candidate rules and a deterministic, data-grounded verification-and-selection loop to enforce statistical validity and deployability constraints.  Across eight clinical prediction tasks, $\\texttt{AgentScore}$ outperforms existing score-generation methods and achieves AUC comparable to more flexible interpretable models despite operating under stronger structural constraints. On two additional externally validated tasks, $\\texttt{AgentScore}$ achieves higher discrimination than established guideline-based scores.","absKo":"현대 clinical practice는 소수의 해석 가능한 decision rule로 구성된 compact scoring system으로 구현되는 evidence-based guideline에 의존한다. machine-learning model은 강한 성능을 보이지만, 많은 모델은 memorability, auditability, bedside execution과 같은 workflow 제약과의 불일치 때문에 일상적인 임상 사용으로 이어지지 못한다. 우리는 이러한 격차가 예측 성능의 부족이 아니라, guideline deployment와 양립할 수 없는 model class를 최적화하기 때문에 발생한다고 주장한다. 배포 가능한 guideline은 흔히 binary rule의 합을 thresholding하여 만든 unit-weighted clinical checklist의 형태를 띠지만, 이러한 score를 학습하려면 가능한 rule set의 지수적으로 큰 discrete space를 탐색해야 한다. 우리는 이 공간에서 LLM을 사용해 candidate rule을 제안하고, deterministic하며 data-grounded한 verification-and-selection loop로 statistical validity와 deployability 제약을 강제하는 semantically guided optimization을 수행하는 $\\texttt{AgentScore}$를 제안한다. 여덟 개의 clinical prediction task 전반에서 $\\texttt{AgentScore}$는 기존 score-generation method보다 우수한 성능을 보이며, 더 유연한 interpretable model에 필적하는 AUC를 더 강한 구조적 제약 하에서도 달성한다. 추가로 외부 검증된 두 task에서는, $\\texttt{AgentScore}$가 확립된 guideline-based score보다 더 높은 discrimination을 달성한다."},{"id":"62829","en":"Ophiuchus: Incentivizing Tool-augmented ''Think with Images'' for Joint Medical Segmentation, Understanding and Reasoning","ko":"Ophiuchus: 의료 Segmentation, Understanding, Reasoning을 통합하는 Tool-augmented \"Think with Images\" 유도","authors":"Yankai Jiang, Yujie Zhang, Peng Zhang, Wenjie Li, Yichen Li, Jintai Chen, Xiaoming Shi, Shihui Zhen","pos":"#701","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=coJqVkqb03","abs":"<p>Recent medical MLLMs have made significant progress in generating step by step textual reasoning chains. However, they still struggle with complex clinical tasks that necessitate dynamic and iterative focusing on fine-grained visual regions. To close this gap, we introduce Ophiuchus, a versatile, tool-augmented framework that equips an MLLM to (i) decide when fine-grained visual evidence is needed, (ii) determine where to probe and ground within the medical image, and (iii) seamlessly weave the relevant sub-image content back into an interleaved, multimodal chain of thought for precise segmentation and diagnosis. Ophiuchus moves beyond mere tool-calling by tightly fusing the MLLM’s inherent grounding and reasoning capabilities with external tools, enabling more accurate and trustworthy decisions. The core of our method is a three-stage training strategy: cold-start SFT for basic tool selection; self-reflection fine-tuning to strengthen decision revision; and agentic tool reinforcement learning to elicit sophisticated, expert-like diagnostic behaviors. Extensive experiments show that Ophiuchus consistently outperforms both closed-source and open-source SOTA methods across diverse medical benchmarks, including VQA, detection, and reasoning-based segmentation.</p>","absKo":"<p>최근 medical MLLM은 단계별 textual reasoning chain을 생성하는 데 큰 진전을 보였다. 그러나 미세한 visual region에 대해 동적으로 그리고 반복적으로 초점을 맞춰야 하는 복잡한 clinical task에서는 여전히 어려움을 겪는다. 이 간극을 메우기 위해, 우리는 MLLM이 (i) 언제 fine-grained visual evidence가 필요한지 판단하고, (ii) medical image 내에서 어디를 probe하고 grounding할지 결정하며, (iii) 관련 sub-image content를 정밀한 segmentation과 diagnosis를 위한 interleaved multimodal chain of thought에 자연스럽게 엮어 넣을 수 있도록 하는 다목적 tool-augmented framework인 Ophiuchus를 제안한다. Ophiuchus는 단순한 tool-calling을 넘어, MLLM의 고유한 grounding 및 reasoning capability를 외부 tool과 긴밀히 결합하여 더 정확하고 신뢰할 수 있는 decision을 가능하게 한다. 우리 방법의 핵심은 세 단계 training strategy이다. 기본적인 tool selection을 위한 cold-start SFT, decision revision을 강화하는 self-reflection fine-tuning, 그리고 정교하고 expert-like한 diagnostic behavior를 이끌어내기 위한 agentic tool reinforcement learning이다. 광범위한 실험은 Ophiuchus가 VQA, detection, reasoning-based segmentation을 포함한 다양한 medical benchmark 전반에서 closed-source 및 open-source SOTA method를 일관되게 능가함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"66549","en":"BioAgent Bench: An AI Agent Evaluation Suite for Bioinformatics","ko":"BioAgent Bench: 생물정보학을 위한 AI 에이전트 평가 스위트","authors":"Dionizije Fa, Marko Culjak, Bruno Pandža, Mateo Cupic","pos":"#816","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=2iFauBXg7Y","abs":"<p>This paper introduces BioAgent Bench, a benchmark dataset and an evaluation suite designed for measuring the performance and robustness of AI agents in common bioinformatics tasks. The benchmark contains curated end-to-end tasks (e.g., RNA-seq, variant calling, metagenomics) with prompts that specify concrete output artifacts to support automated assessment, including stress testing under controlled perturbations. We evaluate frontier closed-source and open-weight models across multiple agent harnesses, and use an LLM-based grader to score pipeline progress and outcome validity. We find that frontier agents can complete multi-step bioinformatics pipelines without elaborate custom scaffolding, often producing the requested final artifacts reliably. However, robustness tests reveal failure modes under controlled perturbations (corrupted inputs, decoy files, and prompt bloat), indicating that correct high-level pipeline construction does not guarantee reliable step-level reasoning. Finally, because bioinformatics workflows may involve sensitive patient data, proprietary references, or unpublished IP, closed-source models can be unsuitable under strict privacy constraints; in such settings, open-weight models may be preferable despite lower completion rates. We release the dataset and evaluation suite publicly.</p>"},{"id":"62965","en":"Understanding Performance Collapse in Layer-Pruned Large Language Models via Decision Representation Transitions","ko":"Layer-Pruned Large Language Models에서 결정 표현 전이로 본 성능 붕괴 이해","authors":"boyu shi, Chang Liu, Chuanbao Gao, Xu Yang, Xin Geng","pos":"#1604","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=bPnEyHvZSu","abs":"<p>Layer pruning efficiently reduces Large Language Model (LLM) computational costs but often triggers sudden performance collapse. Existing representation-based analyses struggle to explain this mechanism. We propose studying pruning through decision representation. Focusing on multiple-choice tasks, we introduce two metrics, Decision Margin and Option Frequency, and an Iterative Pruning method to analyze layer-wise decision dynamics. Our findings reveal a sharp decision transition that partitions the network into two stages: a Silent Phase, where the model cannot yet predict the correct answer, and a Decisive Phase, where the correct prediction emerges. We also find that pruning the Decisive Phase has minimal impact, whereas pruning the Silent Phase triggers immediate performance collapse, highlighting its extreme sensitivity to structural changes. Therefore, we conclude that pruning-induced collapse stems from disrupting the Silent Phase, which prevents the critical decision transition from occurring.</p>","absKo":"<p>Layer pruning은 Large Language Model (LLM)의 연산 비용을 효율적으로 줄이지만, 종종 갑작스러운 성능 붕괴를 유발한다. 기존의 representation 기반 분석으로는 이 메커니즘을 설명하기 어렵다. 우리는 decision representation을 통해 pruning을 연구할 것을 제안한다. multiple-choice task에 초점을 맞추어, layer-wise decision dynamics를 분석하기 위해 Decision Margin과 Option Frequency라는 두 지표와 Iterative Pruning 방법을 도입한다. 우리의 발견은 네트워크를 두 단계로 나누는 급격한 decision transition을 드러낸다. 즉, 모델이 아직 정답을 예측하지 못하는 Silent Phase와, 정답 예측이 나타나는 Decisive Phase이다. 또한 Decisive Phase를 pruning하면 영향이 거의 없지만, Silent Phase를 pruning하면 즉각적인 성능 붕괴가 발생함을 발견했으며, 이는 구조적 변화에 대한 극도의 민감성을 보여준다. 따라서 우리는 pruning으로 인한 붕괴가 Silent Phase를 교란하여 중요한 decision transition이 발생하지 못하게 만드는 데서 비롯된다고 결론짓는다.</p>"},{"id":"60744","en":"Safe and Scalable Web Agent Learning via Recreated Websites","ko":"재현 웹사이트를 통한 안전하고 확장 가능한 Web Agent 학습","authors":"Hyungjoo Chae, Jungsoo Park, Alan Ritter","pos":"#1714","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=x1OLusJLNe","abs":"<p>Training autonomous web agents is fundamentally limited by the environments they learn from: real-world websites are unsafe to explore, hard to reset, and rarely provide verifiable feedback. We propose VeriEnv, a framework that treats language models as environment creators, automatically cloning real-world websites into fully executable, verifiable synthetic environments. By exposing controlled internal access via a Python SDK, VeriEnv enables agents to self-generate tasks with deterministic, programmatically verifiable rewards, eliminating reliance on heuristic or LLM-based judges. This design decouples agent learning from unsafe real-world interaction while enabling scalable self-evolution through environment expansion. Through experiments on web agent benchmarks, we show that agents trained with VeriEnv generalize to unseen websites, achieve site-specific mastery through self-evolving training, and benefit from scaling the number of training environments.</p>","absKo":"<p>자율 web agent를 학습시키는 것은 본질적으로 그들이 학습하는 환경에 의해 제한된다. 실제 웹사이트는 탐색하기에 안전하지 않고, reset하기 어렵고, 검증 가능한 feedback을 거의 제공하지 않는다. 우리는 언어 모델을 environment creator로 취급하여, 실제 웹사이트를 완전히 실행 가능하고 verifiable한 synthetic environment로 자동 복제하는 framework인 VeriEnv를 제안한다. Python SDK를 통해 통제된 내부 접근을 제공함으로써, VeriEnv는 agent가 heuristic 또는 LLM-based judge에 의존하지 않고 결정론적이며 programmatically verifiable한 reward를 갖는 task를 스스로 생성할 수 있게 한다. 이 설계는 unsafe한 실제 환경과의 상호작용에서 agent 학습을 분리하는 동시에, environment expansion을 통한 scalable self-evolution을 가능하게 한다. web agent benchmark에서의 실험을 통해, VeriEnv로 학습한 agent가 보지 못한 웹사이트로 일반화되고, self-evolving training을 통해 사이트별 숙련도를 달성하며, training environment 수의 확장으로부터 이점을 얻음을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"65720","en":"FactGuard: Agentic Video Misinformation Detection via Reinforcement Learning","ko":"FactGuard: 강화학습을 통한 에이전트 기반 영상 허위정보 탐지","authors":"Zehao Li, Hongwei Yu, Hao Jiang, Qiang Sheng, Yilong Xu, Baolong Bi, Yang Li, Zhenlong Yuan, Yujun Cai, Zhaoqi Wang","pos":"#2001","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=AprtLFCirb","abs":"<p>Multimodal large language models (MLLMs) have substantially advanced video misinformation detection through unified multimodal reasoning, but they often rely on fixed-depth inference and place excessive trust in internally generated assumptions, particularly in scenarios where critical evidence is sparse, fragmented, or requires external verification. To address these limitations, we propose FactGuard, an agentic framework for video misinformation detection that formulates verification as an iterative reasoning process built upon MLLMs. FactGuard explicitly assesses task ambiguity and selectively invokes external tools to acquire critical evidence, enabling progressive refinement of reasoning trajectories. To further strengthen this capability, we introduce a two-stage training strategy that combines domain-specific agentic supervised fine-tuning with decision-aware reinforcement learning to optimize tool usage and calibrate risk-sensitive decision making. Extensive experiments on three public benchmarks demonstrate that FactGuard consistently outperforms state-of-the-art methods in both verification accuracy and reliability.</p>"},{"id":"61544","en":"EVOLVING ROLLOUTS: Harnessing Historical Experience for Web Agent Evolution in Reinforcement Learning","ko":"EVOLVING ROLLOUTS: Reinforcement Learning에서 Web Agent 진화를 위한 과거 경험 활용","authors":"Sinuo Wang, WANG PIAOHONG, Tianrui Qin, Maojia Song, Qianben Chen, Qiexiang Wang, Gengze Zhou, Zeyu Zhang, He Zhu, Dingfeng Shi, Yutong Xie, Liam Liu, Jiaheng Liu, Ge Zhang, Jiawei Ma, Yuchen Jiang, Qi Wu, Wangchunshu Zhou","pos":"#214","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=p5B4ABjuT2","abs":"<p>Agentic reinforcement learning (RL) for web search is prohibitively expensive due to long context lengths and costly environment interactions, and this inefficiency is further exacerbated by GRPO-based optimization, which discards learning signals from entire rollout groups with zero reward variance. In this work, we propose EVOLVING ROLLOUTS, an RL framework for web-search agents that moves beyond episodic training and distills collected rollouts into in-context guidance for future policy behavior. By extracting the reward-labeled trajectories into strategic experiences, our method augments standard parameter-space optimization with implicit context-space optimization guided by prior experience. This enables the agent to recover learning signals from zero-variance rollouts, thereby fostering co-evolution between the policy and the experience repository. EVOLVING ROLLOUTS improves sample efficiency and task performance across representative web search benchmarks, enabling Qwen3-4B models to achieve performance comparable to that of the substantially larger Qwen3-30B-A3B model on GAIA, Xbench, and HLE. We open-source our training framework to support reproducibility and future research.</p>","absKo":"<p>웹 검색을 위한 Agentic reinforcement learning (RL)은 긴 context 길이와 비용이 큰 environment interaction 때문에 지나치게 비싸며, zero reward variance를 보이는 전체 rollout group에서 학습 신호를 버리는 GRPO-based optimization 때문에 이러한 비효율은 더욱 심화된다. 본 연구에서는 episodic training을 넘어, 수집된 rollout을 미래 policy behavior를 위한 in-context guidance로 distill하는 웹 검색 agent용 RL framework인 EVOLVING ROLLOUTS를 제안한다. reward로 라벨링된 trajectory를 strategic experience로 추출함으로써, 본 방법은 표준 parameter-space optimization에 prior experience로 guided되는 implicit context-space optimization을 보강한다. 이를 통해 agent는 zero-variance rollout에서 학습 신호를 복원할 수 있으며, 그 결과 policy와 experience repository 간의 co-evolution이 촉진된다. EVOLVING ROLLOUTS는 대표적인 web search benchmark 전반에서 sample efficiency와 task performance를 향상시키며, Qwen3-4B model이 GAIA, Xbench, HLE에서 훨씬 더 큰 Qwen3-30B-A3B model에 견줄 만한 성능을 달성하도록 한다. 우리는 재현성과 향후 연구를 지원하기 위해 training framework를 오픈소스로 공개한다.</p>"},{"id":"63989","en":"AdaMEM: Test-Time Adaptive Memory for Language Agents","ko":"AdaMEM: 언어 에이전트를 위한 테스트 시간 적응형 메모리","authors":"Yunxiang Zhang, Yiheng Li, Ali Payani, Lu Wang","pos":"#2200","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=RzlmkviaNy","abs":"<p>A central challenge for language agents is utilizing past experience to adapt to dynamic test-time conditions. While recent work demonstrates the promise of agentic memory mechanisms, most systems restrict retrieval to episode initiation. Consequently, agents are forced to rely on static guidance that becomes increasingly misaligned as long-horizon tasks unfold. To address this rigidity, we propose the Adaptive Memory Agent (AdaMEM), a novel framework for agent test-time adaptation. Without updating model parameters online, AdaMEM adapts agent behavior via a hybrid memory architecture: it maintains a long-term trajectory memory of raw experiences collected offline while generating dynamic short-term strategy memory on-the-fly to guide decision-making. This mechanism enables the trade-off between token efficiency and adaptability across varying inference-time compute levels. Empirically, AdaMEM significantly outperforms static memory baselines, achieving relative gains of up to 13% on ALFWorld and 11% on WebShop.  To further enhance this adaptation, we develop Step-MFT, a Step-wise Memory Fine-Tuning technique that trains the policy to synthesize high-quality strategies from retrieved experiences, yielding additional performance gains.  Our work establishes a new scaling dimension for agentic memory, supporting continuous reasoning and self-evolution post-deployment in real-world environments.</p>","absKo":"<p>언어 agent가 동적인 test-time 조건에 적응하기 위해 과거 경험을 활용하는 것은 핵심 과제이다. 최근 연구는 agentic memory mechanism의 가능성을 보여주었지만, 대부분의 시스템은 retrieval을 episode 초기화에만 제한한다. 그 결과, agent는 장기 과제가 진행될수록 점점 더 맞지 않게 되는 정적인 guidance에 의존해야 한다. 이러한 경직성을 해결하기 위해, 우리는 agent test-time adaptation을 위한 새로운 framework인 Adaptive Memory Agent (AdaMEM)를 제안한다. AdaMEM은 모델 parameter를 온라인으로 업데이트하지 않으면서도 hybrid memory architecture를 통해 agent behavior를 적응시킨다. 즉, 오프라인에서 수집된 raw experience의 long-term trajectory memory를 유지하는 한편, decision-making을 안내하기 위해 dynamic short-term strategy memory를 즉석에서 생성한다. 이 메커니즘은 다양한 inference-time compute level에서 token efficiency와 adaptability 사이의 trade-off를 가능하게 한다. 실험적으로, AdaMEM은 static memory baseline을 크게 능가하며 ALFWorld에서 최대 13%, WebShop에서 11%의 상대적 향상을 달성한다. 이러한 적응을 더욱 강화하기 위해, 우리는 retrieved experience로부터 고품질 strategy를 합성하도록 policy를 학습하는 Step-wise Memory Fine-Tuning 기법인 Step-MFT를 개발했으며, 이는 추가적인 성능 향상을 가져온다. 우리의 작업은 agentic memory를 위한 새로운 scaling dimension을 확립하며, 실제 환경에서 배포 이후에도 continuous reasoning과 self-evolution을 지원한다.</p>"},{"id":"66670","en":"ArenaRL: Scaling RL for Open-Ended Agents via Tournament-based Relative Ranking","ko":"ArenaRL: 토너먼트 기반 상대 랭킹을 통한 개방형 에이전트용 RL 확장","authors":"Qiang Zhang, Boli Chen, Fanrui Zhang, Ruixue Ding, Shihang Wang, Qiuchen Wang, Yinfeng Huang, Haonan Zhang, Rongxiang Zhu, Xin Li, Houquan zhou, Pengjun Xie, Kaipeng Zhang, Jingren Zhou, Jiawei Liu","pos":"#2207","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=1XUCkpEknR","abs":"Reinforcement learning (RL) has advanced LLM agents on verifiable tasks but remains challenging for open-ended tasks with vast solution spaces (e.g., complex travel planning). Lacking objective ground truth, current RL algorithms rely on reward models assigning scalar scores to individual responses. We contend such pointwise scoring induces discrimination collapse: reward model fails to distinguish subtle advantages among trajectories, compressing intra-group rewards into a narrow range. This drowns effective reward signals in reward model noise, causing optimization stagnation. To address this, we propose ArenaRL, a reinforcement learning paradigm shifting from pointwise scalar scoring to intra-group relative ranking. ArenaRL introduces a process-aware pairwise evaluation with multi-level rubrics for fine-grained relative scoring. Meanwhile, we construct an intra-group adversarial arena and devise a tournament-based ranking scheme to obtain stable advantage signals. ArenaRL achieves high-precision advantage estimation with only $O(N)$ computational complexity, striking a favourable balance between efficiency and accuracy. Furthermore, to address the lack of full-cycle benchmarks for open-ended agents, we introduce two high-quality benchmarks: Open-Travel and Open-DeepResearch, encompassing full training and multi-dimensional evaluation pipelines. Extensive experiments across three open-ended tasks validate the effectiveness of ArenaRL."},{"id":"63226","en":"Optimizing Diversity and Quality through Base-Aligned Model Collaboration","ko":"베이스 정렬 모델 협업을 통한 다양성과 품질 최적화","authors":"Yichen Wang, Chenghao Yang, Tenghao Huang, Muhao Chen, Jonathan May, Mina Lee","pos":"#2511","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Yw55CRYtKo","abs":"<p>Alignment has greatly improved large language models (LLMs)’ output quality at the cost of diversity, yielding highly similar outputs across generations, especially in open-ended generation tasks. We propose Base-Aligned Model Collaboration (BACo), an inference-time token-level model collaboration framework that dynamically combines a base LLM with its aligned counterpart to optimize diversity and quality. Using uncertainty and content-based signals, BACO employs routing strategies to determine, at each token, which model to decode from. Prior diversity-promoting methods often improve diversity at the expense of quality or require expensive decoding or post-training. In contrast, BACO achieves both high diversity and quality post hoc within a single pass, while offering strong controllability. We introduce a family of effective routing strategies and evaluate them across three open-ended generation tasks with 13 diversity and quality metrics. BACo consistently surpasses state-of-the-art inference-time baselines. With our best router, BACo achieves a 21.3% joint improvement in diversity and quality, which is further supported by human evaluations. Overall, our results demonstrate that collaboration between base and aligned models provides an effective and controllable mechanism for optimizing the diversity-quality trade-off.</p>","absKo":"<p>Alignment는 large language model (LLM)의 output quality를 크게 향상시켰지만 다양성을 희생했고, 특히 open-ended generation task에서 생성 간 출력이 매우 유사해졌다. 우리는 Base-Aligned Model Collaboration (BACo)를 제안한다. 이는 inference-time token-level model collaboration framework로, base LLM과 그 aligned counterpart를 동적으로 결합하여 다양성과 품질을 최적화한다. BACo는 uncertainty와 content-based signal을 사용해 각 token마다 어느 model에서 decode할지 결정하는 routing strategy를 사용한다. 기존의 diversity-promoting method는 종종 diversity를 높이는 대신 품질을 떨어뜨리거나, 비용이 큰 decoding 또는 post-training을 필요로 했다. 반면 BACo는 단일 pass 안에서 post hoc으로 높은 다양성과 품질을 모두 달성하며, 뛰어난 controllability도 제공한다. 우리는 효과적인 routing strategy family를 제안하고, 13개의 diversity 및 quality metric을 사용하여 3개의 open-ended generation task 전반에서 평가한다. BACo는 state-of-the-art inference-time baseline을 일관되게 능가한다. 가장 좋은 router를 사용할 때, BACo는 diversity와 quality의 공동 향상율 21.3%를 달성하며, 이는 human evaluation으로도 뒷받침된다. 전반적으로 우리의 결과는 base model과 aligned model의 collaboration이 diversity-quality trade-off를 최적화하는 효과적이고 통제 가능한 메커니즘을 제공함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"65106","en":"MusicDET: Zero-Shot AI-Generated Music Detection","ko":"MusicDET: Zero-Shot AI 생성 음악 탐지","authors":"Chaolei Han, Hongsong Wang, Jie Gui","pos":"#3102","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=GiYWL2NVKs","abs":"<p>Detecting AI-generated music is crucial for preserving artistic authenticity and preventing the misuse of generative music technologies. However, existing discriminative detectors typically rely on generated samples during training and often suffer from severe performance degradation when confronted with music produced by unseen generators, which limits their real-world applicability. To address this issue, we formulate a zero-shot setting for AI-generated music detection, where the detector is trained exclusively on real music without access to any generated samples. Under this setting, we propose MusicDET, a generator-agnostic detection framework based on frequency-guided normalizing flows that probabilistically models the distribution of real music features. By evaluating the likelihood of an input sample under the learned real-music distribution, MusicDET enables effective detection of out-of-distribution music signals. Experiments on the FakeMusicCaps and SONICS datasets show that MusicDET consistently outperforms conventional discriminative detectors, particularly when detecting music generated by previously unseen models.</p>"},{"id":"61968","en":"Does AI Reviewer See the Full Picture? Attacking and Defending Multimodal Peer Review","ko":"AI 리뷰어는 전체 그림을 볼 수 있을까? 멀티모달 peer review의 공격과 방어","authors":"Xinyu Zhao, Rana Khan, Zhen Xu, Zhen Tan, Tianlong Chen","pos":"#3108","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=l8RBjihPFk","abs":"<p>The formal integration of Large Language Models (LLMs) and Multimodal LLMs (MLLMs) into scientific peer-review workflows introduces novel and significant risks. Their safety against adversarial manipulation remains critically underexplored, especially given the multimodal nature of scientific papers where figures, not just text, convey core evidence. This creates a significant gap: current robustness studies are overwhelmingly text-only, and the problem is distinct from standard jailbreaking, as a peer-review attack seeks to induce a domain-specific, targeted failure (e.g., \"inflate this score\") rather than a general safety policy violation, for which no practical defenses exist. To address this, we introduce PaperGuard, the first comprehensive benchmark designed to systematically evaluate and defend AI-generated peer review against these domain-specific, cross-modal attacks. Our framework is built on three pillars: (1) a new multimodal peer-review dataset spanning multiple scientific domains; (2) a unified suite of attacks, including black-box prompt injections and white-box perturbations, specifically designed to target both text (GCG) and figures (PGD); and (3) a practical defense, motivated by the long-context challenge of academic papers, that uses chunk-based embedding search to efficiently localize and mitigate harmful instructions. Our extensive experiments, conducted across state-of-the-art models, confirm that these systems are pervasively vulnerable. PaperGuard establishes the foundational benchmark, protocols, and actionable defense necessary to pioneer trustworthy, attack-resilient AI-assisted scholarly reviewing.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large Language Models(LLMs)와 Multimodal LLMs(MLLMs)를 과학적 peer-review 워크플로에 형식적으로 통합하는 것은 새롭고 중대한 위험을 초래한다. 특히 과학 논문의 핵심 증거는 텍스트뿐 아니라 figure에도 담겨 있으므로, adversarial manipulation에 대한 안전성은 여전히 결정적으로 덜 탐구되어 있다. 이로 인해 중요한 공백이 생긴다. 현재의 robustness 연구는 압도적으로 text-only이며, 문제 자체도 표준 jailbreaking과 다르다. peer-review 공격은 일반적인 safety policy 위반이 아니라 도메인 특화된 표적 실패(예: \"이 점수를 부풀려라\")를 유도하려는 것이며, 이에 대한 실용적 방어는 존재하지 않는다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 PaperGuard를 제안한다. 이는 AI 생성 peer review를 이러한 도메인 특화 cross-modal 공격에 대해 체계적으로 평가하고 방어하도록 설계된 최초의 포괄적 benchmark이다. 우리의 프레임워크는 세 가지 축 위에 구축된다. (1) 여러 과학 도메인을 아우르는 새로운 multimodal peer-review dataset; (2) text(GCG)와 figure(PGD) 모두를 겨냥하도록 특별히 설계된 black-box prompt injection과 white-box perturbation을 포함하는 통합 공격 모음; (3) 학술 논문의 long-context 문제에서 착안한 실용적 방어로, chunk-based embedding search를 사용해 유해한 지시를 효율적으로 국소화하고 완화한다. 최첨단 모델 전반에 걸친 광범위한 실험은 이러한 시스템이 광범위하게 취약함을 확인한다. PaperGuard는 신뢰할 수 있고 공격에 강인한 AI 보조 학술 심사를 개척하는 데 필요한 기초 benchmark, 프로토콜, 그리고 실행 가능한 방어를 확립한다.</p>"},{"id":"62034","en":"Large Language Model Agents Are Not Always Faithful Self-Evolvers","ko":"LLM Agents는 항상 충실한 Self-Evolver가 아니다","authors":"Weixiang Zhao, Yingshuo Wang, Yichen Zhang, Yang Deng, Yanyan Zhao, Wanxiang Che, Bing Qin, Ting Liu","pos":"#3406","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=kTjSSqgqGf","abs":"<p>Self-evolving large language model (LLM) agents continually improve by accumulating and reusing past experience, yet it remains unclear whether they faithfully rely on that experience to guide their behavior. We present the first systematic investigation of \\emph{experience faithfulness}—the causal dependence of an agent's decisions on the experience it is given—in self-evolving LLM agents. Using controlled causal interventions on both raw and condensed forms of experience, we comprehensively evaluate four representative frameworks across 10 LLM backbones and 9 environments. Our analysis uncovers a striking asymmetry: while agents consistently depend on raw experience, they often disregard or misinterpret condensed experience, even when it is the only experience provided. This gap persists across single- and multi-agent configurations and across backbone scales. We trace its underlying causes to three factors: the semantic limitations of condensed content, internal processing biases that suppress experience, and task regimes where pretrained priors already suffice. These findings challenge prevailing assumptions about self-evolving methods and underscore the need for more faithful and reliable approaches to experience integration.</p>","absKo":"<p>Self-evolving large language model (LLM) agents는 과거 경험을 축적하고 재사용하면서 지속적으로 성능을 향상시키지만, 실제로 그 경험에 충실하게 의존해 행동하는지는 여전히 불분명하다. 우리는 self-evolving LLM agents에서 agent의 의사결정이 주어진 경험에 얼마나 인과적으로 의존하는지를 뜻하는 \\emph{experience faithfulness}를 체계적으로 처음 조사한다. raw experience와 condensed experience 모두에 대해 통제된 인과 개입을 적용하여, 10개의 LLM backbone과 9개의 환경에서 4개의 대표적 framework를 종합적으로 평가했다. 분석 결과는 놀라운 비대칭성을 드러낸다. agent들은 raw experience에는 일관되게 의존하지만, condensed experience는 그것이 유일하게 제공된 경우에도 종종 무시하거나 잘못 해석한다. 이러한 격차는 single-agent와 multi-agent 구성 모두, 그리고 backbone scale 전반에서 지속된다. 우리는 그 근본 원인을 세 가지 요인으로 추적한다: condensed content의 의미론적 한계, experience를 억제하는 내부 처리 bias, 그리고 pretrained prior만으로도 충분한 task regime이다. 이러한 결과는 self-evolving method에 대한 통상적 가정에 의문을 제기하며, experience integration을 더 faithful하고 reliable하게 만드는 접근의 필요성을 강조한다.</p>"},{"id":"61830","en":"ADEPT: RL-Aligned Agentic Decoding of Emotion via Evidence Probing Tools — From Consensus Learning to Ambiguity-Driven Emotion Reasoning","ko":"ADEPT: Evidence Probing Tool을 통한 RL 정렬 Agentic 감정 디코딩 — Consensus Learning에서 모호성 기반 감정 추론까지","authors":"Esther Sun, Bo-Hao Su, Abinay Reddy Naini, Shinji Watanabe, Carlos Busso","pos":"#3409","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=maA1s1S0db","abs":"<p>Speech Large Language Models (SLLMs) enable high-level emotion reasoning, but often produce ungrounded, text-biased judgments without verifiable acoustic evidence. In contrast, SSL encoders such as WavLM yield strong acoustic representations yet remain opaque discriminative models that offer limited interpretability. To bridge this gap, we introduce the Agentic Decoding of Emotion via Probing Tools (ADEPT) framework, which reframes emotion recognition as a multi-turn inquiry process rather than a single-pass prediction. ADEPT transforms an SLLM into an agent that maintains an evolving candidate set and adaptively invokes dedicated semantic and acoustic probing tools within a structured pipeline of candidate generation, evidence collection, and adjudication. Crucially, ADEPT enables a paradigm shift from consensus learning to ambiguity-driven emotion reasoning. Since human affect exhibits complexity and co-occurrence of emotions, we leverage minority annotations as informative signals instead of discarding them as noise. Finally, we integrate Group Relative Policy Optimization (GRPO) with the Evidence Trust Gate to explicitly couple tool-usage behaviors with prediction quality and enforce evidence-based reasoning. Experiments demonstrate that ADEPT improves in most cases the primary emotion accuracy while substantially improving minor emotion characterization, producing explanations grounded in auditable evidence.</p>","absKo":"<p>Speech Large Language Models (SLLMs)는 높은 수준의 emotion reasoning을 가능하게 하지만, 검증 가능한 acoustic evidence 없이 근거가 부족하고 text에 치우친 판단을 내리는 경우가 많다. 반면 WavLM과 같은 SSL encoder는 강력한 acoustic representation을 제공하지만, 해석 가능성이 제한된 불투명한 discriminative model로 남아 있다. 이 간극을 메우기 위해 우리는 emotion recognition을 단일 패스 prediction이 아니라 다중 턴 inquiry process로 재구성하는 Agentic Decoding of Emotion via Probing Tools (ADEPT) framework를 제안한다. ADEPT는 SLLM을 후보 집합을 점진적으로 유지하고, candidate generation, evidence collection, adjudication으로 이루어진 구조화된 pipeline 내에서 전용 semantic 및 acoustic probing tool을 적응적으로 호출하는 agent로 변환한다. 특히 ADEPT는 consensus learning에서 ambiguity-driven emotion reasoning으로의 패러다임 전환을 가능하게 한다. 인간의 affect는 복잡하며 여러 emotion이 동시에 나타날 수 있으므로, 우리는 minority annotation을 noise로 버리지 않고 유용한 신호로 활용한다. 마지막으로, Group Relative Policy Optimization (GRPO)과 Evidence Trust Gate를 통합하여 tool 사용 행동과 prediction quality를 명시적으로 결합하고 evidence-based reasoning을 강제한다. 실험은 ADEPT가 대부분의 경우 primary emotion accuracy를 개선하는 동시에 minor emotion characterization도 크게 향상시키며, 검증 가능한 evidence에 근거한 설명을 생성함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"63107","en":"Bridging the Stability-Expressivity Gap: Synthetic Data Scaling and Preference Alignment for Low-Resource Spoken Language Models","ko":"안정성-표현력 격차 해소: 저자원 음성 언어 모델을 위한 합성 데이터 확장과 선호도 정렬","authors":"Yizhong Geng, Yanliang Li, Jinghan Yang, Tianhan Jiang, Boxun An, Ya Li, Xiaoyu Shen","pos":"#3604","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=a57NvkgjT2","abs":"<p>Spoken Language Models (SLMs) revolutionize speech synthesis by bypassing traditional linguistic front-ends, yet they remain limited by the digital resource disparities across languages. We investigate these challenges within the Southeast Asian linguistic landscape, using the phonetically complex Thai and data-scarce Lao as representative cases for low-resource SLMs. Scaling experiments reveal that reliance on synthetic data triggers a Stability-Expressivity Gap, characterized by a non-monotonic degradation we term Synthetic Erosion. To bridge this gap, we propose two self-alignment frameworks. Disentanglement-Guided Self-Alignment (DGSA) recovers expressivity for complex languages by exploiting prosody-timbre separation. For regimes where authentic references are exceptionally limited, Temperature-Driven Self-Critique (TDSC) stabilizes generation through automated exploration and filtering. Our methods achieve state-of-the-art results, including the first zero-shot voice cloning capability for Lao, establishing a scalable pathway for high-fidelity synthesis across the global linguistic long-tail. Audio Samples are available at: \\url{https://anonymous.4open.science/api/repo/multilantts-demo-EEF6/file/index.html?v=2de23271}.</p>","absKo":"<p>Spoken Language Models (SLMs)는 전통적인 linguistic front-end를 우회함으로써 speech synthesis를 혁신하지만, 언어 간 디지털 자원 격차로 인해 여전히 제약을 받는다. 우리는 저자원 SLMs의 대표 사례로 음운적으로 복잡한 Thai와 데이터가 부족한 Lao를 사용하여, 동남아시아 언어 환경 내에서 이러한 문제를 조사한다. Scaling experiment는 synthetic data에 대한 의존이 Stability-Expressivity Gap을 유발하며, 우리가 Synthetic Erosion이라 부르는 비단조적 성능 저하로 특징지어짐을 보여준다. 이 격차를 메우기 위해 우리는 두 가지 self-alignment framework를 제안한다. Disentanglement-Guided Self-Alignment (DGSA)는 prosody-timbre separation을 활용하여 복잡한 언어의 expressivity를 복원한다. 진짜 reference가 극도로 제한된 환경에서는 Temperature-Driven Self-Critique (TDSC)가 자동 탐색과 필터링을 통해 generation을 안정화한다. 우리의 방법은 state-of-the-art 결과를 달성하며, 여기에는 Lao에 대한 최초의 zero-shot voice cloning capability도 포함된다. 이는 전 세계 언어 long-tail 전반에서 고충실도 synthesis를 위한 확장 가능한 경로를 제시한다. Audio Samples는 다음에서 확인할 수 있다: \\url{https://anonymous.4open.science/api/repo/multilantts-demo-EEF6/file/index.html?v=2de23271}.</p>"},{"id":"62794","en":"ToolOrchestra: Elevating Intelligence via Efficient Model and Tool Orchestration","ko":"ToolOrchestra: 효율적인 모델 및 Tool Orchestration으로 지능 향상","authors":"Hongjin SU, Shizhe Diao, Ximing Lu, Mingjie Liu, Jiacheng Xu, Xin Dong, Yonggan Fu, Peter Belcak, Hanrong Ye, Hongxu (Danny) Yin, Yi Dong, Evelina Bakhturina, Tao Yu, Yejin Choi, Jan Kautz, Pavlo Molchanov","pos":"#3609","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=dDVla2lLTA","abs":"Large language models are powerful generalists, yet solving deep and complex problems such as those of the Humanity’s Last Exam (HLE) remains both conceptually challenging and computationally expensive. We show that small orchestrators managing other models and a variety of tools are able to both push the upper bound of intelligence and improve efficiency in solving difficult agentic tasks. We introduce ToolOrchestra, a method for training small orchestrators that coordinate the use of intelligent tools. ToolOrchestra makes explicit use of reinforcement learning with outcome-, efficiency-, and user-preference-aware rewards. Using ToolOrchestra, we produce Orchestrator, an 8B model that achieves higher accuracy at lower cost than previous tool-use agents while aligning with user preferences on which tools are to be used for a given query. On HLE, Orchestrator achieves a score of 37.1%, outperforming GPT-5 (35.1%) while being 2.5x more efficient. On $\\tau ^2$-Bench and FRAMES, Orchestrator surpasses GPT-5 by a wide margin while using only about 30% of the cost. Extensive analysis shows that Orchestrator achieves the best trade-off between performance and cost under multiple metrics, and generalizes robustly to previously unseen tools. These results demonstrate that composing diverse tools with a lightweight orchestration model is both more efficient and more effective than existing methods, paving the way for practical and scalable tool-augmented reasoning systems. These results demonstrate that orchestrating diverse tools with lightweight agents is not only more efficient, but also more effective, paving the way for practical and scalable tool-augmented reasoning systems.","absKo":"대형 언어 모델은 강력한 범용성이 있지만, Humanity’s Last Exam(HLE)과 같은 심층적이고 복잡한 문제를 해결하는 일은 개념적으로도 어렵고 계산 비용도 크다. 우리는 다른 모델과 다양한 tool을 관리하는 작은 orchestrator가 지능의 상한을 끌어올리는 동시에 어려운 agentic task를 더 효율적으로 풀 수 있음을 보인다. 우리는 지능형 tool의 사용을 조율하는 작은 orchestrator를 학습시키는 방법인 ToolOrchestra를 소개한다. ToolOrchestra는 outcome-, efficiency-, user-preference-aware reward를 사용한 reinforcement learning을 명시적으로 활용한다. ToolOrchestra를 사용해 우리는 Orchestrator라는 8B model을 만들었으며, 이는 주어진 query에 대해 어떤 tool을 사용할지에 대한 user preference와 정렬되면서도, 이전 tool-use agent보다 더 낮은 비용으로 더 높은 정확도를 달성한다. HLE에서 Orchestrator는 37.1%의 점수를 기록하여 GPT-5(35.1%)를 능가하면서 2.5배 더 효율적이다. $\\tau ^2$-Bench와 FRAMES에서는 Orchestrator가 GPT-5를 큰 차이로 앞서면서도 비용은 약 30%만 사용한다. 광범위한 분석은 Orchestrator가 여러 metric에서 performance와 cost 사이의 최선의 trade-off를 달성하고, 이전에 보지 못한 tool에도 강건하게 일반화함을 보여준다. 이러한 결과는 다양한 tool을 lightweight orchestration model과 결합하는 것이 기존 방법보다 더 효율적이고 더 효과적임을 보여주며, 실용적이고 확장 가능한 tool-augmented reasoning system으로 가는 길을 연다. 이러한 결과는 다양한 tool을 lightweight agent로 조율하는 것이 더 효율적일 뿐 아니라 더 효과적이기도 하다는 점을 보여주며, 실용적이고 확장 가능한 tool-augmented reasoning system으로 가는 길을 연다."},{"id":"66577","en":"Hybrid-Gym: Training Coding Agents to Generalize Across Tasks","ko":"Hybrid-Gym: 작업 전반에 걸쳐 일반화하도록 코딩 에이전트 훈련","authors":"Yiqing Xie, Emmy Liu, Gaokai Zhang, Nachiket Kotalwar, Shubham Gandhi, Acharya, Xingyao Wang, Carolyn Rose, Graham Neubig, Daniel Fried","pos":"#400","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=2TVSJxxz9u","abs":"<p>Coding agents are increasingly used for a wide range of real-world tasks, from adding features and documentation to creating programs from scratch. Ideally, the agent should perform well across all the diverse tasks. However, most prior work concentrates on issue solving, and such single-task training does not transfer reliably to other coding tasks. In this work, we aim to train coding agents that generalize across tasks. We first analyze task transferability from two axes: the commonalities shared among coding tasks and the capabilities of current agents. Guided by these findings, we derive a set of principles for training task design and verify them through a series of controlled experiments. We then present Hybrid-Gym, a training dataset built on four scalable training tasks that follow these principles. Experiments show that, under zero-shot task transfer, Hybrid-Gym achieves performance comparable to in-domain training, and further improves existing datasets when combined with them (e.g., +4.85% on SWT-Bench-Verified).</p>"},{"id":"61305","en":"IntentRL: Training Proactive User-intent Agents for Open-ended Deep Research via Reinforcement Learning","ko":"IntentRL: Reinforcement Learning으로 개방형 심층 연구를 위한 선제적 사용자 의도 Agent 학습","authors":"Haohao Luo, Zexi Li, Yuexiang Xie, Wenhao Zhang, Yaliang Li, Ying Shen","pos":"#401","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=rWSwu2Req3","abs":"<p>Deep Research (DR) agents extend Large Language Models (LLMs) beyond parametric knowledge by autonomously retrieving and synthesizing evidence from large web corpora into long-form reports, enabling a long-horizon agentic paradigm. However, unlike real-time conversational assistants, DR is computationally expensive and time-consuming, creating an autonomy-interaction dilemma: high autonomy on ambiguous user queries often leads to prolonged execution with unsatisfactory outcomes. To address this, we propose IntentRL, a framework that trains proactive agents to clarify latent user intents before starting long-horizon research. To overcome the scarcity of open-ended research data, we introduce a scalable pipeline that expands a few seed samples into high-quality dialogue turns via a shallow-to-deep intent refinement graph. We further adopt a two-stage reinforcement learning (RL) strategy: Stage I applies RL on offline dialogues to efficiently learn general user-interaction behavior, while Stage II uses the trained agent and a user simulator for online rollouts to strengthen adaptation to diverse user feedback. Extensive experiments show that IntentRL significantly improves both intent hit rate and downstream task performance, outperforming the built-in clarify modules of closed-source DR agents and proactive LLM baselines.</p>","absKo":"<p>Deep Research (DR) agent는 Large Language Models (LLMs)를 parametric knowledge를 넘어 확장하여, 대규모 web corpus에서 증거를 자율적으로 검색하고 종합해 long-form report로 구성함으로써 long-horizon agentic paradigm을 가능하게 한다. 그러나 실시간 대화형 assistant와 달리 DR은 계산 비용과 시간이 많이 들기 때문에, autonomy-interaction dilemma를 야기한다. 즉, 모호한 user query에 대해 높은 autonomy를 부여하면 종종 실행이 길어지고 결과는 만족스럽지 못하다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 IntentRL을 제안한다. 이 framework는 장기 연구를 시작하기 전에 latent user intent를 명확히 하도록 proactive agent를 학습시킨다. open-ended research data의 부족을 극복하기 위해, 우리는 shallow-to-deep intent refinement graph를 통해 소수의 seed sample을 고품질 dialogue turn으로 확장하는 확장 가능한 pipeline을 도입한다. 또한 우리는 두 단계 reinforcement learning (RL) 전략을 채택한다. Stage I에서는 offline dialogue에 대해 RL을 적용해 일반적인 user-interaction behavior를 효율적으로 학습하고, Stage II에서는 학습된 agent와 user simulator를 사용해 online rollout을 수행함으로써 다양한 user feedback에 대한 적응성을 강화한다. 광범위한 실험 결과, IntentRL은 intent hit rate와 downstream task performance를 모두 크게 향상시키며, closed-source DR agent의 내장 clarify module 및 proactive LLM baseline을 능가한다.</p>"},{"id":"65020","en":"Minimizing Mismatch Risk: A Prototype-Based Routing Framework for Zero-shot LLM-generated Text Detection","ko":"불일치 위험 최소화: Zero-shot LLM 생성 텍스트 탐지를 위한 Prototype 기반 Routing 프레임워크","authors":"Ke Sun, Guangsheng Bao, Han Cui, Yue Zhang","pos":"#4011","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Hh1hf4kauu","abs":"<p>Zero-shot methods detect LLM-generated text by computing statistical signatures using a surrogate model. Existing approaches typically employ a fixed surrogate for all inputs regardless of the unknown source. We systematically examine this design and find that detection performance varies substantially depending on surrogate-source alignment. We observe that while no single surrogate achieves optimal performance universally, a well-matched surrogate typically exists within a diverse pool for any given input. This finding transforms robust detection into a routing problem: selecting the most appropriate surrogate for each input. We propose DetectRouter, a prototype-based framework that learns text-detector affinity through two-stage training. The first stage constructs discriminative prototypes from white-box models; the second generalizes to black-box sources by aligning geometric distances with observed detection scores. Experiments on EvoBench and MAGE benchmarks demonstrate consistent improvements across multiple detection criteria and model families.</p>"},{"id":"66718","en":"Learning to Route Languages for Multilingual Preference Optimization","ko":"다국어 Preference Optimization을 위한 언어 라우팅 학습","authors":"Geyang Guo, Hiromi Wakaki, Yuki Mitsufuji, Alan Ritter, Wei Xu","pos":"#402","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=13lMChKB5u","abs":"<p>Large language models (LLMs) are trained on heterogeneous multilingual corpora, yet existing preference optimization methods often implicitly restrict each training question to a single response language or rely on a fixed dominant language for supervision.  We propose language-routed preference optimization (LRPO), an online preference optimization framework that treats language as a selectable variable rather than a fixed input constraint.  LRPO elicits multilingual rollouts for each training question and integrates their relative quality into preference-based policy updates, increasing the diversity and informativeness of training signals under the fixed rollout budget.  To adaptively determine which languages to explore, we introduce a trainable language router formulated as a multi-armed bandit, balancing exploration of underutilized languages with exploitation of more informative ones. Extensive experiments show that LRPO consistently improves multilingual performance, demonstrating that adaptive language routing enables effective cross-lingual knowledge exploitation for training.</p>"},{"id":"60632","en":"Scaling Laws in Model Fine-tuning for Audio DeepFake Detection","ko":"오디오 DeepFake 탐지를 위한 모델 Fine-tuning의 Scaling Law","authors":"Xiang Li, Pin-Yu Chen, Wenqi Wei","pos":"#403","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=yHT8piYc8u","abs":"<p>Recent advances in audio deepfake detection have been driven by increasingly large speech foundation models and growing amounts of synthetic data. Despite steady improvements on different benchmarks, it remains unclear how detection performance scales with model capacity and training data under realistic deployment conditions, where detectors operate under distribution shift, signal corruption, and unseen synthesis pipelines. In this work, we present the first systematic study of scaling laws in post-training audio deepfake detection, focusing on fine-tuning regimes rather than large-scale pretraining.  Using a controlled family of speech foundation models with shared architecture and pretraining, we analyze how detection performance, robustness, and generalization evolve as a function of model size and training data scale. Our evaluation covers multiple dimensions, including out-of-distribution datasets, common audio corruptions, cross-language generalization, and cross-TTS (Text-to-Speech) generalization to unseen speech synthesis systems. Across settings, we observe consistent but highly non-uniform scaling behavior: while larger models are more sample-efficient and generalize better overall, scaling benefits weaken under corruptions and linguistic shift, and persistent error gaps remain even at the largest scales.  Our results reveal a fundamental asymmetry between performance scaling and robustness scaling in audio deepfake detection. While larger detectors consistently improve in-distribution detection performance, gains in robustness and generalization, particularly under cross-language and cross-TTS evaluation, are substantially weaker and exhibit persistent error gaps.</p>","absKo":"<p>최근 audio deepfake detection의 발전은 점점 더 큰 speech foundation model과 증가하는 synthetic data에 의해 주도되어 왔다. 여러 benchmark에서 꾸준한 향상이 있었음에도, detector가 distribution shift, signal corruption, unseen synthesis pipeline 하에서 동작하는 실제 배포 조건에서 model capacity와 training data에 따라 detection 성능이 어떻게 scaling되는지는 여전히 불분명하다. 이 연구에서 우리는 large-scale pretraining이 아니라 fine-tuning regime에 초점을 맞춰 post-training audio deepfake detection에서의 scaling law에 대한 최초의 체계적 연구를 제시한다. 공유 architecture와 pretraining을 가진 통제된 speech foundation model family를 사용하여, model size와 training data scale의 함수로서 detection 성능, robustness, generalization이 어떻게 진화하는지 분석한다. 우리의 평가는 out-of-distribution dataset, 일반적인 audio corruption, cross-language generalization, 그리고 unseen speech synthesis system에 대한 cross-TTS (Text-to-Speech) generalization을 포함한 여러 차원을 포괄한다. 다양한 설정 전반에서 우리는 일관적이지만 매우 비균일한 scaling behavior를 관찰한다. 더 큰 모델은 sample efficiency가 높고 전반적으로 generalization이 더 좋지만, corruption과 linguistic shift 하에서는 scaling의 이점이 약해지며, 가장 큰 규모에서도 지속적인 error gap이 남아 있다. 우리의 결과는 audio deepfake detection에서 성능 scaling과 robustness scaling 사이의 근본적 비대칭성을 드러낸다. 더 큰 detector는 in-distribution detection 성능을 일관되게 향상시키는 반면, 특히 cross-language 및 cross-TTS 평가에서 robustness와 generalization의 향상은 훨씬 약하고 지속적인 error gap을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"65929","en":"EGG: An Expert-Guided Agent Framework for Kernel Generation","ko":"EGG: 커널 생성을 위한 전문가 유도 에이전트 프레임워크","authors":"Yaochen Han, Ke Fan, Hongxu Jiang, Wanqi Xu, Weiyu Xie, Runhua Zhang, Chenhui Zhu, Yixiang Zhang","pos":"#500","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=8nti23Zqkt","abs":"High-performance GPU kernels are critical for reducing the exponentially growing computational costs of large language models (LLMs), but their development heavily relies on manual tuning by domain experts. While recent advances in LLM-based approaches show promise for automating kernel generation, they still struggle to achieve both correctness and high performance. This limitation primarily arises from the lack of domain-specific optimization guidance, hindering effective exploration of the optimization space. We propose $\\textbf{EGG}$, an $\\underline{E}$xpert-$\\underline{G}$uided Agent Framework for Kernel $\\underline{G}$eneration, which incorporates expert optimization principles to guide LLMs’ decisions. Inspired by expert workflows, we decompose kernel generation into two hierarchical stages: 1) algorithmic structure design, which establishes a high-quality computational structure foundation; 2) hardware-specific tuning, which performs targeted adjustments through parallel mapping, tensor tiling, and memory optimization. This staged decomposition defines explicit optimization objectives, structuring the design space to achieve progressive refinements. To this end, a stage-aware multi-agent collaboration mechanism is designed for inter and intra-stage context management, ensuring stable optimization trajectories. Experiments on KernelBench and real-world workloads show that EGG achieves a $2.13\\times$ average speedup over PyTorch, outperforming existing agent-based and RL-based approaches."},{"id":"64615","en":"Convex Low-resource Accent-Robust Language Detection in Speech Recognition","ko":"음성 인식에서의 Convex 저자원 Accent-Robust 언어 탐지","authors":"Miria Feng, William H. Tan, Mert Pilanci","pos":"#501","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=LezLGW8UFX","abs":"<p>Globalization and multiculturalism continue to produce increasingly diverse speech varieties. Yet current spoken dialogue systems frequently fail on under-represented dialects and accents, often misidentifying the input language and causing cascading failures in downstream dialogue tasks. Addressing this dialectal variance under low-resource constraints remains an open challenge, as standard fine-tuning is computationally expensive and prone to overfitting on high-dimensional speech data. We propose Convex Language Detection (CLD), a novel framework that integrates theoretically grounded convex optimization techniques into the spoken dialogue systems pipeline. Our method is efficiently implemented via multi-GPU Alternating Direction Method of Multipliers (ADMM) in JAX, thus providing global optimality guarantees and fast training in polynomial time. Theoretically, we prove that our convex objective induces certified margin stability and provide rigorous guarantees against feature perturbations. Empirically, we demonstrate sample efficiency and robustness to input dialectical variance, to significantly reduce language misidentification rates for low-resource dialects within high-resource languages. Our open-source package is available at \\url{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/CLD-845F/README.md}.</p>","absKo":"<p>세계화와 다문화주의는 점점 더 다양한 speech variety를 만들어내고 있다. 그러나 현재의 spoken dialogue system은 대표성이 낮은 dialect와 accent에서 자주 실패하며, 입력 언어를 잘못 식별해 downstream dialogue task에서 연쇄적인 실패를 일으키곤 한다. 저자원 제약하에서 이러한 dialectal variance를 다루는 것은 여전히 열린 과제로 남아 있는데, 표준 fine-tuning은 계산 비용이 높고 고차원 speech data에서 overfitting에 취약하기 때문이다. 우리는 이론적으로 정당화된 convex optimization 기법을 spoken dialogue system pipeline에 통합한 새로운 framework인 Convex Language Detection (CLD)을 제안한다. 우리의 방법은 JAX에서 multi-GPU Alternating Direction Method of Multipliers (ADMM)로 효율적으로 구현되며, 이를 통해 global optimality guarantee와 polynomial time의 빠른 학습을 제공한다. 이론적으로, 우리는 우리의 convex objective가 certified margin stability를 유도함을 증명하고, feature perturbation에 대한 엄밀한 보장을 제공한다. 경험적으로, 우리는 sample efficiency와 입력 dialectical variance에 대한 강건성을 입증하여, 고자원 언어 내 저자원 dialect에 대한 language misidentification rate를 크게 줄인다. 우리의 open-source package는 \\url{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/CLD-845F/README.md}에서 제공된다.</p>"},{"id":"62395","en":"CRPO: Character-centric Group Relative Policy Optimization for Role-aware Reasoning in Role-playing Agents","ko":"CRPO: 역할 연극 에이전트의 역할 인식 추론을 위한 Character-centric Group Relative Policy Optimization","authors":"Yihong Tang, Kehai Chen, Liang Yue, Benyou Wang, Min zhang","pos":"#502","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=h2JyEuY6OL","abs":"<p>Recent advancements in Reinforcement Learning (RL), particularly Group Relative Policy Optimization (GRPO), have significantly enhanced the reasoning capabilities of Large Language Models. However, applying these problem-centric optimization methods to role-playing agents often leads to a loss of character fidelity and style collapse, as they prioritize context-specific utility over persona alignment. To address this, we propose Character-Centric Group Relative Policy Optimization (CRPO), a framework designed to realign RL objectives with the role-playing task. CRPO improves character distinctiveness through three mechanisms: decoupling task logic from stylistic rewards to resolve gradient conflicts, dynamically adapting optimization constraints based on character complexity, and utilizing generic responses as negative baselines to prevent the model from reverting to a common distribution. Extensive experiments demonstrate that CRPO outperforms existing methods in consistency, emotion and others.</p>","absKo":"<p>Reinforcement Learning (RL), 특히 Group Relative Policy Optimization (GRPO)의 최근 발전은 Large Language Models의 추론 능력을 크게 향상시켰다. 그러나 이러한 problem-centric 최적화 방법을 role-playing agent에 적용하면, context-specific utility를 persona alignment보다 우선시하기 때문에 character fidelity의 손실과 style collapse가 발생하는 경우가 많다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 RL 목표를 role-playing task에 다시 정렬하도록 설계된 framework인 Character-Centric Group Relative Policy Optimization (CRPO)을 제안한다. CRPO는 세 가지 메커니즘을 통해 캐릭터의 구별성을 향상시킨다. 즉, task logic과 stylistic reward를 분리하여 gradient conflict를 해소하고, character complexity에 따라 optimization constraint를 동적으로 조정하며, generic response를 negative baseline으로 활용하여 모델이 공통 분포로 되돌아가는 것을 방지한다. 광범위한 실험은 CRPO가 일관성, 감정 및 기타 측면에서 기존 방법을 능가함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"65399","en":"Black-Box Detection of LLM-Generated Text Using Generalized Jensen Shannon Divergence","ko":"일반화된 Jensen Shannon Divergence를 이용한 LLM 생성 텍스트의 블랙박스 탐지","authors":"Shuangyi Chen, Ashish Khisti","pos":"#503","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=E2kWotHfT7","abs":"<p>We study black-box detection of machine-generated text under practical constraints: the scoring model (proxy LM) may mismatch the unknown source model, and per-input contrastive generation is costly. We propose SurpMark, a reference-based detector that summarizes a passage by the dynamics of its token surprisals. SurpMark discretizes surprisals into interpretable states, estimates a state-transition matrix for the test text, and scores it via a generalized Jensen–Shannon (GJS) gap between the test transitions and two fixed references (human vs. machine) built once from existing corpora. Theoretically, we derive design guidance for how the discretization bins should scale with data and provide a principled justification for our test statistic. Empirically, across multiple datasets, source models, and scenarios, SurpMark consistently matches or surpasses baselines, demonstrating strong robustness across domains and generators; our experiments on hyperparameter sensitivity exhibit trends that our theoretical results help to explain.</p>"},{"id":"66065","en":"Uncertainty-Aware Clarification in LLM Agents with Information Gain","ko":"정보 이득을 활용한 LLM 에이전트의 불확실성 인식 명료화","authors":"Mengyi DENG, Zhiwei Li, Xin Li, Tingyu ZHU, Ying Zhao, Zhijiang Guo, Wei Wang","pos":"#405","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=7N2ydbDahV","abs":"Large Language Model (LLM) agents often operate under underspecified user instructions, where latent uncertainty over user intent leads to erroneous tool actions. To address this challenge, we propose a goal-oriented clarification framework that aligns clarification behavior with ambiguity resolution. Central to our approach is the Information Gain Reward, a metric that quantifies the utility of clarification questions by measuring the Bayesian belief update towards the ground-truth goal induced by the clarification exchange. We train the clarifier (LLM) using this reward to optimize for high information gain, ensuring that clarifications effectively reduce uncertainty and improve task completion within the agent-tool-user environment. We validate our framework within a clarification-enhanced $\\tau$-Bench environment, conducting cross-agent evaluations across five heterogeneous backbones. Empirical results demonstrate that our method consistently improves the success rate by 3.7\\% over the no-clarification baseline, incurring small overhead via surgical interventions (averaging only 0.3 additional steps). Our code and data are available at the anonymous repository: \\url{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/Information-Gain-Clarifier-AD68/}."},{"id":"63981","en":"Improving Neural Topic Modeling with Semantically-Grounded Soft Label Distributions","ko":"의미 기반 soft label 분포로 신경 토픽 모델링 개선","authors":"Raymond Li, Amirhossein Abaskohi, Chuyuan Li, Gabriel Murray, Giuseppe Carenini","pos":"#4100","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=S2PARGuQzI","abs":"<p>Traditional neural topic models are typically optimized by reconstructing the document's Bag-of-Words (BoW) representations, overlooking contextual information and struggling with data sparsity. In this work, we propose a novel approach to construct semantically-grounded soft label targets using Language Models (LMs) by projecting the next token probabilities, conditioned on a specialized prompt, onto a pre-defined vocabulary to obtain contextually enriched supervision signals. By training the topic models to reconstruct the soft labels using the LM hidden states, our method produces higher-quality topics that are more closely aligned with the underlying thematic structure of the corpus. Experiments on three datasets show that our method achieves substantial improvements in topic coherence, purity over existing baselines. Additionally, we also introduce a retrieval-based metric, which shows that our approach significantly outperforms existing methods in identifying semantically similar documents, highlighting its effectiveness for retrieval-oriented applications.\\footnote{we will release the code upon publishing the paper.}</p>","absKo":"<p>전통적인 neural topic model은 일반적으로 문서의 Bag-of-Words (BoW) 표현을 재구성하도록 최적화되며, 이 과정에서 문맥 정보를 간과하고 데이터 희소성에 취약하다. 본 연구에서는 특수한 prompt에 조건화된 Language Models (LMs)의 next token probabilities를 미리 정의된 vocabulary에 projection하여 의미적으로 grounded된 soft label target을 구성하는 새로운 접근법을 제안한다. 이를 통해 문맥적으로 풍부한 supervision signal을 얻을 수 있다. LM hidden states를 사용하여 soft label을 재구성하도록 topic model을 학습하면, 본 방법은 corpus의 근본적인 thematic structure와 더 밀접하게 정렬된 더 높은 품질의 topic을 생성한다. 세 개의 데이터셋에서 수행한 실험은 본 방법이 기존 baseline 대비 topic coherence와 purity를 크게 향상시킴을 보여준다. 또한 retrieval-based metric도 도입하는데, 이는 본 접근이 의미적으로 유사한 문서를 식별하는 데서 기존 방법을 현저히 능가함을 보여주며, retrieval-oriented application에서의 효과를 강조한다.\\footnote{we will release the code upon publishing the paper.}</p>"},{"id":"64668","en":"From Shortcuts to Reasoning: Robust Post-Training of Theory of Mind with Reinforcement Learning","ko":"지름길에서 추론으로: Reinforcement Learning을 활용한 Theory of Mind의 강건한 Post-Training","authors":"Jike Zhong, Yuxiang Lai, Ming Li, Yuheng Li, Wuao Liu, Behzad Dariush, Konstantinos Psounis, Shao-Yuan Lo","pos":"#4310","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=L3fJXwaFdx","abs":"<p>Theory of Mind (ToM) is a must-acquire skill for modern foundation model systems to operate effectively and safely in the real world. Recent works have explored honing ToM via post-training; however, we show that such progress is confounded by a pervasive “shortcut” issue: tasks can reach up to 99% accuracy by simply exploiting spurious causal correlations, leading to a false sense of ToM. Motivated by this, we first develop a framework to systematically examine ToM datasets for shortcuts and provide guidance for future development. We find that questions reducible to pure state tracking (e.g., “belief”) are especially shortcut-prone compared to mind questions (e.g., “intention”) where reasoning beyond tracking is required. Using four shortcut-free datasets across three ToM contexts, we then comprehensively study whether reinforcement-learning fine-tuning with verifiable rewards and explicit reasoning (Thinking-RFT) elevates ToM beyond supervised fine-tuning (SFT). Our key findings are: 1) Thinking-RFT effectively improves ToM in all scenarios (+6% vs. SFT), particularly in complex higher-order reasoning (+10% vs. SFT) and multimodal cases (+7% vs. SFT), and generalizes notably better to unseen domains and higher-order queries while being more robust to counterfactuals. 2) ToM benefits specifically from the joint effect of reasoning and RL: Thinking-RFT outperforms No-Thinking-RFT by 7% on average. 3) RFT works by learning to ground its reasoning on anchor cues (keywords/state changes) that correspond to causal factors. We believe our study is useful for developing effective and robust ToM post-training datasets and advancing critical ToM capabilities in foundation models.</p>","absKo":"<p>Theory of Mind(ToM)는 현대 foundation model 시스템이 실제 세계에서 효과적이고 안전하게 작동하기 위해 반드시 습득해야 하는 능력이다. 최근 연구들은 post-training을 통해 ToM을 향상시키는 방법을 탐구해 왔지만, 우리는 그러한 진전이 만연한 “shortcut” 문제에 의해 혼동될 수 있음을 보인다. 즉, task는 단지 허위 causal correlation을 이용하는 것만으로도 최대 99% accuracy에 도달할 수 있어, ToM에 대한 잘못된 인상을 낳는다. 이러한 문제의식에서, 우리는 먼저 ToM dataset에서 shortcut을 체계적으로 점검하고 향후 개발을 위한 지침을 제공하는 framework를 구축한다. 그 결과 순수한 state tracking으로 환원되는 질문(예: “belief”)은 tracking을 넘어서는 reasoning이 필요한 mind 질문(예: “intention”)에 비해 특히 shortcut에 취약함을 확인한다. 이어서 세 가지 ToM context에 걸친 네 개의 shortcut-free dataset을 사용해, 검증 가능한 reward와 explicit reasoning을 결합한 reinforcement-learning fine-tuning(Thinking-RFT)이 supervised fine-tuning(SFT)보다 ToM을 더 향상시키는지 종합적으로 분석한다. 주요 결과는 다음과 같다. 1) Thinking-RFT는 모든 시나리오에서 ToM을 효과적으로 개선하며(SFT 대비 +6%), 특히 복잡한 higher-order reasoning(+10% vs. SFT)과 multimodal case(+7% vs. SFT)에서 두드러지고, 보지 못한 domain과 higher-order query로의 generalization이 더 좋으며 counterfactual에 대해서도 더 robust하다. 2) ToM은 reasoning과 RL의 결합 효과로부터 특히 이득을 보며, Thinking-RFT는 No-Thinking-RFT보다 평균 7% 높다. 3) RFT는 causal factor에 대응하는 anchor cue(키워드/state change)에 reasoning을 grounding하도록 학습함으로써 작동한다. 우리는 본 연구가 효과적이고 robust한 ToM post-training dataset을 설계하고 foundation model의 핵심 ToM 능력을 발전시키는 데 유용하다고 믿는다.</p>"},{"id":"62654","en":"MindZero: Learning Online Mental Reasoning With Zero Annotations","ko":"MindZero: Zero Annotations 기반 온라인 Mental Reasoning 학습","authors":"Shunchi Zhang, Jin Lu, Chuanyang Jin, Yichao Zhou, Zhining Zhang, Tianmin Shu","pos":"#412","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=efbZ2Qe2D8","abs":"<p>Effective real-world assistance requires AI agents with robust Theory of Mind (ToM): inferring human mental states from their behavior. Despite recent advances, several key challenges remain, including (1) online inference with robust uncertainty updates over multiple hypotheses; (2) efficient reasoning suitable for real-time assistance; and (3) the lack of ground-truth mental state annotations in real-world domains. We address these challenges by introducing <em>MindZero</em>, a self-supervised reinforcement learning framework that trains language models to perform efficient and robust online mental reasoning. During training, the model is rewarded for generating mental state hypotheses that maximize the likelihood of observed actions estimated by a planner, similar to model-based ToM reasoning. This method thus eliminates the need for explicit mental state annotations. After training, <em>MindZero</em> internalizes model-based reasoning, and performs mental inference in a single forward pass at test time. We evaluate <em>MindZero</em> in four challenging mental reasoning and AI assistance domains. <em>MindZero</em> matches the robustness of explicit model-based methods while significantly accelerating inference, outperforming state-of-the-art methods by a large margin. These results demonstrate that mental reasoning can be learned as a self-supervised skill, bridging the gap between robustness and efficiency in ToM modeling.</p>","absKo":"<p>실효성 있는 현실 세계 assistance에는 robust Theory of Mind (ToM)를 갖춘 AI agent가 필요하다. 즉, 행동으로부터 인간의 mental state를 추론할 수 있어야 한다. 최근의 진전에도 불구하고, 여러 핵심 과제가 여전히 남아 있다. 여기에는 (1) 여러 hypothesis에 걸친 robust uncertainty update를 포함하는 online inference, (2) 실시간 assistance에 적합한 efficient reasoning, 그리고 (3) 현실 세계 도메인에서의 ground-truth mental state annotation 부재가 포함된다. 우리는 language model이 efficient하고 robust한 online mental reasoning을 수행하도록 학습하는 self-supervised reinforcement learning framework인 <em>MindZero</em>를 도입함으로써 이러한 과제들을 해결한다. 학습 중 모델은 planner가 추정한 관측된 action의 likelihood를 최대화하는 mental state hypothesis를 생성하도록 보상받으며, 이는 model-based ToM reasoning과 유사하다. 이 방법은 explicit mental state annotation의 필요성을 제거한다. 학습 후 <em>MindZero</em>는 model-based reasoning을 internalize하며, 테스트 시 단일 forward pass로 mental inference를 수행한다. 우리는 네 가지 어려운 mental reasoning 및 AI assistance 도메인에서 <em>MindZero</em>를 평가한다. <em>MindZero</em>는 explicit model-based method의 robustness에 필적하면서 inference를 크게 가속하고, state-of-the-art method들을 큰 폭으로 능가한다. 이러한 결과는 mental reasoning이 self-supervised skill로 학습될 수 있음을 보여주며, ToM modeling에서 robustness와 efficiency 사이의 간극을 메운다.</p>"},{"id":"65732","en":"SVL: Empowering Spiking Neural Networks for Efficient 3D Open-World Understanding","ko":"SVL: 효율적 3D 개방형 세계 이해를 위한 Spiking Neural Network 강화","authors":"Xuerui Qiu, Shaowei Gu, Peixi Wu, JiaKui Hu, Yaozhi Wen, Yuqi Pan, Xinhao Luo, Bo XU, Guoqi Li","pos":"#2710","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Ai3a79cTvr","abs":"<p>Spiking Neural Networks (SNNs) offer an energy--efficient route to 3D spatio--temporal perception, yet they lag behind Artificial Neural Networks (ANNs) due to weak pretraining and heavy inference stacks, limiting generalization and multimodal reasoning (e.g., zero--shot 3D classification and open--world QA). We present a universal \\textbf{S}pike--based \\textbf{V}ision--\\textbf{L}anguage pretraining framework (SVL) that equips SNNs with open--world 3D understanding while preserving end--to--end spike efficiency. SVL comprises two core components: (i) {Multi--scale Triple Alignment} (MTA), a label--free triplet contrastive objective aligning 3D, image, and text; and (ii) {Re--parameterizable Vision--Language Integration} (Rep--VLI), which converts offline text embeddings into lightweight weights for text--encoder--free inference. Moreover, we present the first fully spike--driven point Transformer, {Spike-driven PointFormer}, whose 3D spike--driven self--attention (3D-SDSA) reduces interactions to sparse additions, enabling faster, more efficient training. Extensive experiments show that SVL attains strong zero--shot 3D classification (85.4% top--1) and consistently outperforms prior SNNs on downstream tasks (e.g., +6.1% 3D cls, +2.1% DVS actions, +1.1% detection, +2.1% segmentation) while enabling open--world 3D question answering, sometimes outperforming ANNs. To the best of our knowledge, SVL represents the first scalable, generalizable, and hardware-friendly paradigm for 3D open-world understanding, effectively bridging the gap between SNNs and ANNs in complex open-world understanding tasks.</p>"},{"id":"66327","en":"A$^2$SG: Adaptive and Asymmetric Surrogate Gradients for Training Deep Spiking Neural Network","ko":"A$^2$SG: 심층 Spiking Neural Network 훈련을 위한 적응적 비대칭 대리 그래디언트","authors":"Yechan Kang, Yongjin Kweon, Mingyeong Seo, Sohee Park, Yeonguk jeon, Jongkil Park, Seungmo Yang, Jaewook Kim, Yeonjoo Jeong, Suyoun Lee, Seongsik Park","pos":"#3000","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=4fX2DEypNL","abs":"Training deep spiking neural networks (SNNs) remains challenging due to sharp loss landscapes and temporal inconsistency caused by surrogate gradients. To address these challenges, we propose a unified framework: adaptive and asymmetric surrogate gradients (A$^2$SG). The adaptive gradients adjust an effective window for spatio-temporal adaptation, reducing spatial gradient variation and maintaining directional consistency of gradients over time. The asymmetric gradients reflect neuronal dynamics by assigning larger gradients to neurons with higher membrane potentials, and we prove that they yield lower variation than symmetric surrogates. Our analysis further establishes a direct connection between local gradient variation and the curvature of the loss landscape, providing a principled explanation for how A$^2$SG promotes convergence to flatter minima and improves generalization. We conduct extensive experiments on diverse models, including CNN-based and Transformer-based SNNs, across various tasks such as image classification using both static and neuromorphic datasets, as well as segmentation. The results demonstrate that A$^2$SG consistently improves accuracy and energy efficiency, establishing it as a general and reliable solution for training deep SNNs."},{"id":"65430","en":"ViEEG: Hierarchical Visual Neural Representation for EEG Brain Decoding","ko":"ViEEG: EEG 뇌 디코딩을 위한 계층적 시각 신경 표현","authors":"Minxu Liu, Donghai Guan, Chuhang Zheng, Chunwei Tian, Jie Wen, Qi Zhu","pos":"#308","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=DkK7GUr8n3","abs":"<p>Understanding and decoding brain activity into visual representations is a fundamental challenge at the intersection of neuroscience and artificial intelligence. While electroencephalogram (EEG) visual decoding has shown promise due to its non-invasive and low-cost nature, existing methods suffer from Hierarchical Neural Encoding Neglect (HNEN), a critical limitation in which flat neural representations fail to model the brain’s hierarchical visual processing. Inspired by the hierarchical organization of visual cortex, we propose ViEEG, a neuro-inspired framework that addresses HNEN. ViEEG decomposes each visual stimulus into three biologically aligned components, namely contour, foreground object, and contextual scene, which serve as anchors for a three-stream EEG encoder. These EEG features are progressively integrated via cross-attention routing, simulating cortical information flow from low-level to high-level vision. We further adopt hierarchical contrastive learning for EEG-CLIP representation alignment, enabling zero-shot object recognition. Extensive experiments on THINGS-EEG dataset demonstrate that ViEEG significantly outperforms previous methods by a large margin in both subject-dependent and subject-independent settings. Results on THINGS-MEG dataset further confirm ViEEG's generalization to different neural modalities. Our framework not only advances the performance frontier but also sets a new paradigm for EEG brain decoding. Code and pretrained models will be available.</p>"},{"id":"64520","en":"UniSparse: Combining Weight Pruning and Spike Sparsification in Spiking Neural Networks","ko":"UniSparse: 스파이킹 신경망에서 가중치 가지치기와 스파이크 희소화 결합","authors":"Xinyu Shi, Tong Bu, Zhaofei Yu","pos":"#309","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=MliujooUya","abs":"<p>Spiking Neural Networks (SNNs) offer a notable energy-saving advantage compared to Artificial Neural Networks (ANNs) when deployed on neuromorphic hardware. While recent SNNs achieve superior performance using larger and deeper backbones, this comes at a cost of diminishing their energy-saving benefits. In this paper, we propose UniSparse, a unified sparsification framework for enhancing the energy efficiency of SNNs. We demonstrate that the affine parameters in batch normalization also serve as the learnable threshold of its subsequent spiking neurons. Based on this, we propose a novel spike sparsification method that reduces firing rate by constraining the affine parameters. As a complement to spike sparsification, we propose a weight pruning method based on the same energy constraint, which can be naturally integrated with spike sparsification. Experimental results demonstrate that UniSparse achieves a state-of-the-art trade-off between accuracy and energy efficiency across models and datasets. The sparsified ResNet-18 model requires only 7.04M SOPs for inference to achieve 92.38\\% accuracy on the CIFAR-10 dataset. Our work highlights the great potential of deep SNNs in improving energy efficiency.</p>","absKo":"<p>Spiking Neural Networks (SNNs)는 neuromorphic hardware에 배포될 때 Artificial Neural Networks (ANNs)와 비교하여 두드러진 에너지 절감 이점을 제공한다. 최근 SNN은 더 크고 깊은 backbone을 사용하여 뛰어난 성능을 달성하고 있지만, 이는 에너지 절감 이점을 약화시키는 비용을 수반한다. 본 논문에서는 SNN의 에너지 효율을 향상시키기 위한 통합 sparsification 프레임워크인 UniSparse를 제안한다. 우리는 batch normalization의 affine parameter가 이후 spiking neuron의 learnable threshold 역할도 한다는 점을 보인다. 이를 바탕으로 affine parameter를 제약하여 firing rate를 낮추는 새로운 spike sparsification 방법을 제안한다. spike sparsification의 보완책으로, 동일한 energy constraint를 기반으로 한 weight pruning 방법을 제안하며, 이는 spike sparsification과 자연스럽게 통합될 수 있다. 실험 결과, UniSparse는 모델과 데이터셋 전반에서 accuracy와 energy efficiency 사이의 state-of-the-art trade-off를 달성한다. sparsified ResNet-18 모델은 CIFAR-10 데이터셋에서 92.38\\% accuracy를 달성하는 데 inference 시 단 7.04M SOPs만을 필요로 한다. 우리의 연구는 deep SNN이 에너지 효율 향상에 지닌 큰 잠재력을 강조한다.</p>"},{"id":"62569","en":"Training Deep Spiking Neural Networks without Normalization","ko":"정규화 없이 Deep Spiking Neural Network 학습","authors":"Xinyu Shi, Zhaofei Yu","pos":"#310","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=fSV4XWhMB3","abs":"<p>The training of deep Spiking Neural Networks (SNNs) has traditionally relied on Batch Normalization (BN), which stabilizes input currents and gradients during training. However, BN is not a universal solution. It is unsuitable for variable-length tasks and scenarios with reduced batch size, constraining the development of deep SNNs, where removing BN typically causes the training to fail to converge. This dependence stems not from a fundamental necessity of BN but from the current lack of reasonable initialization methods for SNNs. This paper addresses this core limitation by proposing SpikeInit, a novel initialization framework for SNNs. By modeling the response curve and gradient of spiking layers, SpikeInit initializes the weights and shape parameters of surrogate gradients to maintain stable firing rates during forward propagation and stable gradient magnitudes during backpropagation. Extensive experiments demonstrate that deep SNNs with SpikeInit can be trained stably without normalization and achieve superior performance compared to their normalized counterparts under identical settings. Furthermore, we demonstrate the scalability of SpikeInit by successfully training an ultra-deep, 1000-layer SNN without normalization. Our work provides a foundational step toward large-scale normalization-free SNN, liberating SNN design from the constraints of normalization.</p>","absKo":"<p>Deep Spiking Neural Network (SNN)의 학습은 전통적으로 Batch Normalization (BN)에 의존해 왔으며, BN은 학습 동안 입력 전류와 gradient를 안정화한다. 그러나 BN은 만능 해결책이 아니다. 이는 가변 길이 작업과 batch size가 줄어든 상황에는 부적합하며, BN을 제거하면 학습이 수렴하지 않는 경우가 많아 deep SNN의 개발을 제약한다. 이러한 의존성은 BN의 근본적 필요성에서 비롯된 것이 아니라, 현재 SNN에 대한 합리적인 initialization 방법이 부족하기 때문이라고 볼 수 있다. 본 논문은 SNN을 위한 새로운 initialization framework인 SpikeInit을 제안함으로써 이 핵심 한계를 해결한다. Spike layer의 response curve와 gradient를 모델링하여, SpikeInit은 forward propagation 동안 안정적인 firing rate와 backpropagation 동안 안정적인 gradient 크기를 유지하도록 weight와 surrogate gradient의 shape parameter를 초기화한다. 광범위한 실험은 SpikeInit을 적용한 deep SNN이 normalization 없이도 안정적으로 학습될 수 있으며, 동일한 설정에서 normalized counterpart보다 우수한 성능을 달성함을 보여준다. 더 나아가, normalization 없이 1000-layer의 ultra-deep SNN을 성공적으로 학습시켜 SpikeInit의 확장성도 입증한다. 우리의 연구는 대규모 normalization-free SNN을 향한 기초적 단계를 제공하며, normalization의 제약으로부터 SNN 설계를 해방한다.</p>"},{"id":"62184","en":"Temporal Weighted Encoding: Towards Maximal-Capacity Spike Coding for ANN–SNN Conversion","ko":"Temporal Weighted Encoding: ANN–SNN 전환을 위한 최대 용량 Spike Coding 추구","authors":"Yiwen Gu, Junchuan Gu, Haibin Shen, Kejie Huang","pos":"#311","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ixb50TfWoM","abs":"<p>Spiking Neural Networks (SNNs) emulate the spiking behavior of biological neurons and are promising for energy-efficient neuromorphic computing. A widely used strategy to train SNNs is to convert pretrained Artificial Neural Networks (ANNs), where the accuracy and efficiency are determined by the spike encoding scheme. Traditional methods based on spike count or timing severely underutilize the available encoding space, leading to large accuracy degradation under low-timestep constraints. More expressive alternatives involve complex dynamics, which hinder scalability and practical deployment. To address these challenges, we propose Temporal Weighted Encoding (TWE). Through a simple recursive integration, spikes are implicitly assigned exponentially decaying weights, drawing an analogy to a temporal bit sequence. We systematically analyze the temporal mismatch caused by this weight pattern and propose temporal relaxation and threshold relaxation to resolve this issue, enabling fast and accurate activation encoding. Extensive experiments demonstrate that TWE achieves negligible conversion loss with significantly fewer timesteps, offering a scalable and efficient solution for SNN deployment.</p>","absKo":"<p>Spiking Neural Networks(SNNs)는 생물학적 neuron의 spiking behavior를 모사하며, 에너지 효율적인 neuromorphic computing에 유망하다. SNN을 학습하는 널리 쓰이는 전략은 pretrained Artificial Neural Networks(ANNs)를 변환하는 것이며, 이때 정확도와 효율성은 spike encoding scheme에 의해 결정된다. spike count나 timing에 기반한 전통적 방법은 사용 가능한 encoding space를 심각하게 저활용하여, 낮은 timestep 제약 하에서 큰 정확도 저하를 초래한다. 더 표현력이 풍부한 대안은 복잡한 dynamics를 수반하는데, 이는 확장성과 실용적 배포를 저해한다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 Temporal Weighted Encoding(TWE)을 제안한다. 단순한 recursive integration을 통해 spike에 지수적으로 감쇠하는 가중치가 암묵적으로 부여되며, 이는 temporal bit sequence에 비유될 수 있다. 우리는 이 가중치 패턴이 야기하는 temporal mismatch를 체계적으로 분석하고, 이를 해결하기 위해 temporal relaxation과 threshold relaxation을 제안하여 빠르고 정확한 activation encoding을 가능하게 한다. 광범위한 실험은 TWE가 훨씬 더 적은 timestep으로 conversion loss를 거의 유발하지 않으면서, SNN deployment를 위한 확장 가능하고 효율적인 솔루션을 제공함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"64012","en":"SpikingLM: Towards Fully Spiking Language Model","ko":"SpikingLM: 완전한 Spiking Language Model을 향하여","authors":"Yu Liang, Zijian Zhou, Wenjie Wei, Shuai Wang, Honglin Cao, Ammar Belatreche, Yu Yang, Malu Zhang, Yang Yang, Haizhou Li","pos":"#312","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=RirE9gm77w","abs":"<p>Spiking Neural Networks (SNNs) offer a promising avenue toward energy-efficient language modeling by replacing multiply-accumulate operations with sparse, event-driven computation. However, constructing fully spiking language models reveals two fundamental challenges: (1) gradient degradation from dead neurons caused by diminishing input magnitudes in deep networks, and (2) reduced token selectivity due to the absence of softmax's competitive winner-takes-all mechanism. These limitations create a substantial performance gap that has hindered the practical deployment of spiking language models. To address these challenges, we introduce SpikingLM, a framework that bridges the efficiency of SNNs with the capabilities of modern language models through two key innovations. First, we propose Distribution-aware Scaling, which rescales linear outputs to an optimal range that prevents gradient vanishing. These parameters are fused into preceding linear layers at inference, incurring zero additional overhead. Second, we introduce Spike2Max, a hardware-efficient attention mechanism that restores winner-takes-all dynamics through base-2 exponentiation and max-subtraction. By exploiting the integer-valued nature of spike coincidence counts, Spike2Max replaces floating-point exponentials with bit-shift operations, reducing attention energy consumption by over 95\\% compared to softmax. Extensive experiments demonstrate that SpikingLM achieves a 57.9\\% reduction in energy consumption while delivering state-of-the-art performance on GLUE among spiking language models.</p>","absKo":"<p>Spiking Neural Networks(SNNs)는 multiply-accumulate 연산을 sparse한 event-driven computation으로 대체함으로써 energy-efficient language modeling을 위한 유망한 경로를 제공한다. 그러나 완전한 spiking language model을 구성하면 두 가지 근본적인 문제가 드러난다. (1) 깊은 네트워크에서 입력 크기가 감소하면서 dead neuron이 발생해 gradient degradation이 생기고, (2) softmax의 경쟁적 winner-takes-all 메커니즘이 없어 token selectivity가 저하된다. 이러한 한계는 spiking language model의 실용적 배포를 가로막아 온 상당한 성능 격차를 만든다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 SNN의 효율성과 현대 language model의 성능을 두 가지 핵심 혁신으로 연결하는 프레임워크인 SpikingLM을 제안한다. 첫째, 우리는 Distribution-aware Scaling을 제안하여 linear output을 gradient vanishing을 방지하는 최적 범위로 재스케일링한다. 이 매개변수는 inference 시 이전 linear layer에 fusion되어 추가 오버헤드가 전혀 없다. 둘째, 우리는 base-2 exponentiation과 max-subtraction을 통해 winner-takes-all 동역학을 복원하는 hardware-efficient attention mechanism인 Spike2Max를 도입한다. spike coincidence count의 정수값 특성을 활용하여, Spike2Max는 floating-point exponential을 bit-shift operation으로 대체하며 softmax 대비 attention energy consumption을 95\\% 이상 줄인다. 광범위한 실험은 SpikingLM이 spiking language model 중 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성하면서 energy consumption을 57.9\\% 줄임을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"66461","en":"Spike-HTR: Spiking Neural Transformer for Handwritten Text Recognition","ko":"Spike-HTR: 필기 텍스트 인식을 위한 Spiking Neural Transformer","authors":"Xiubo Liang, Jinxing Han, Yuke Li, Haoqi Zhu, Yu Zhao, Hongzhi Wang","pos":"#313","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=3UcWAgr0jx","abs":"Offline handwritten text recognition (HTR) is blank-dominated: task-relevant evidence lies in sparse ink strokes, yet mainstream recognizers still expend dense spatial compute and full-length width-axis token mixing across the canvas. Spiking neural networks (SNNs) promise activity-proportional computation, but static inputs make common frame repetition redundant and stochastic coding unstable under small timestep budgets. We propose Spike-HTR, a budgeted spiking Transformer that controls two coupled knobs: the spiking horizon $T$ and the effective token length $\\ell_b$ after blank-guided reduction. InkCoder deterministically gates a shared static stem feature to form a stable coarse-to-fine temporal stream, and a stop-gradient CTC preview drives a CTC-aware keep-and-merge reducer to shorten the width-axis token stream before deep mixing. Trained from scratch without external pretraining, Spike-HTR reaches a rapid-response operating point and achieves $T{=}2$ val/test CERs of 3.5/5.4 on IAM, 2.3/2.5 on LAM, and 4.2/3.9 on READ2016. The implementation and scripts are included in the supplementary material."},{"id":"63522","en":"Spik4lite: Refactoring Neuromorphic Sparsity for Efficient Spiking Neural Networks on Commodity Edge Devices","ko":"Spik4lite: 범용 엣지 디바이스에서 효율적인 Spiking Neural Networks를 위한 뉴로모픽 희소성 재구성","authors":"Yongzhi She, Qihua Zhou, Yuhao Wang, Yaodong Huang, Jingcai Guo, Laizhong Cui","pos":"#314","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=WRP7d18h9t","abs":"<p>Recently, the spiking neural networks (SNNs) have shown great promise in enhancing AI task performance by utilizing the brain-inspired and energy-efficient computational paradigm via the binary (0/1) spikes. Modern SNNs, especially those based on transformers, often require FPGA accelerators or neuromorphic chips (e.g., Intel Loihi) to enable spike-driven computations. However, this domain-specific hardware is not always accessible on commodity edge devices like NVIDIA Jetsons, which may degrade SNNs' energy efficiency due to massive computational waste on inactive \"0\" spikes and finally undermine the usage boundary. This limitation raises an interesting question: is it possible to make SNNs edge-friendly and tame the computations mostly on active \"1\" spikes? In this paper, we present the answer yes and propose Spik4lite, which serves as a lightweight plug-and-play module to significantly improve SNN's performance between model accuracy and computational efficiency. The key is to refactor SNN's channel-wise neuromorphic sparsity by zeroing out low-efficiency channels while proactively compensating for the eliminated spikes. Different from prior methods mainly focusing on optimizing the theoretical synaptic operations, our design philosophy can evolve the SNNs into a physically compact manner, thus inherently saving more computational and energy costs. Extensive experiments based on real edge devices show that Spik4lite can be integrated into existing SNN baselines to further improve their accuracy-and-efficiency performance, guaranteeing the model accuracy while saving the computational and energy costs.</p>","absKo":"<p>최근 spiking neural networks(SNNs)는 바이너리(0/1) spike를 활용하는 뇌 모사형이며 에너지 효율적인 계산 패러다임을 통해 AI 작업 성능 향상에 큰 가능성을 보여주었다. 최신 SNN, 특히 transformer 기반 SNN은 spike-driven computation을 구현하기 위해 FPGA accelerator나 neuromorphic chip(예: Intel Loihi)을 필요로 하는 경우가 많다. 그러나 이러한 도메인 특화 하드웨어는 NVIDIA Jetson과 같은 범용 edge device에서는 항상 사용할 수 있는 것이 아니며, 그 결과 비활성 \"0\" spike에 대한 대규모 계산 낭비로 인해 SNN의 에너지 효율이 저하되고 결국 사용 경계가 약화될 수 있다. 이 한계는 흥미로운 질문을 던진다. SNN을 edge-friendly하게 만들고 계산을 주로 활성 \"1\" spike에 맞추는 것이 가능한가? 본 논문에서는 그 답이 가능하다고 제시하며, 모델 정확도와 계산 효율 사이에서 SNN 성능을 크게 향상시키는 경량 plug-and-play 모듈인 Spik4lite를 제안한다. 핵심 아이디어는 효율이 낮은 채널을 0으로 만들고 제거된 spike를 능동적으로 보상함으로써 SNN의 채널 단위 neuromorphic sparsity를 재구성하는 것이다. 주로 이론적 synaptic operation 최적화에 초점을 맞춘 기존 방법들과 달리, 우리의 설계 철학은 SNN을 물리적으로 더 컴팩트한 형태로 진화시켜 본질적으로 더 많은 계산 및 에너지 비용을 절감하게 한다. 실제 edge device에 기반한 광범위한 실험은 Spik4lite가 기존 SNN 베이스라인에 통합되어 정확도와 효율 성능을 더 향상시킬 수 있으며, 모델 정확도를 보장하면서 계산 및 에너지 비용을 절감함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"63665","en":"SmoothSpike: Spiking Transformer with Learnable Hadamard Transformation","ko":"SmoothSpike: 학습 가능한 Hadamard 변환을 갖는 spiking Transformer","authors":"Zijian Zhou, Wenjie Wei, Yu Liang, Jialin Li, Ammar Belatreche, Honglin Cao, Shuai Wang, Malu Zhang, Yang Yang, Haizhou Li","pos":"#315","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=UoUKCLHjRa","abs":"<p>Spiking Neural Networks (SNNs) that leverage sparse binary spikes and temporal dynamics have emerged as energy-efficient alternatives to Artificial Neural Networks (ANNs). However, SNNs suffer from limited representational capacity due to the discrete nature of spikes.  Existing solutions extending spike levels often overlook the constraints of the simulation time window, leading to a critical issue we identify as spike saturation-induced information homogenization. In this phenomenon, distinct high-amplitude inputs result in identical maximized spike counts, truncating the dynamic range and hindering the model’s ability to capture fine-grained semantic differences. To address this, we propose SmoothSpike, a novel method designed to enhance representational capacity by suppressing spike saturation. We first introduce a randomized Hadamard transformation to smooth neuronal inputs, theoretically proving its efficacy in constraining extreme values and reducing both saturation probability and input variability among saturated neurons. To further improve adaptability, we evolve this into a learnable orthogonal transformation. Initialized with Hadamard matrices and maintained orthogonal via Newton-Schulz iteration, this module dynamically adapts to varying input distributions during training.  Extensive experiments on language modeling tasks show that SmoothSpike effectively mitigates the information homogenization problem and improves task performance. This positions SmoothSpike as a robust solution to bridge the performance gap between SNNs and ANNs.</p>","absKo":"<p>sparse binary spike와 temporal dynamics를 활용하는 Spiking Neural Networks(SNNs)는 Artificial Neural Networks(ANNs)에 대한 energy-efficient 대안으로 부상했다. 그러나 SNN은 spike의 discrete한 특성 때문에 제한된 representational capacity를 가진다. spike level을 확장하는 기존 해법들은 simulation time window의 제약을 간과하는 경우가 많으며, 그 결과 spike saturation-induced information homogenization이라는 우리가 식별한 치명적인 문제가 발생한다. 이 현상에서는 서로 다른 고진폭 입력이 동일한 최대 spike count로 귀결되어 dynamic range가 잘리고, 모델이 세밀한 의미 차이를 포착하는 능력이 저해된다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 spike saturation을 억제하여 representational capacity를 향상시키도록 설계된 새로운 방법인 SmoothSpike를 제안한다. 우리는 먼저 randomized Hadamard transformation을 도입하여 neuronal input을 smooth하게 만들고, 극단값을 제한하며 saturated neuron들 사이의 saturation probability와 input variability를 모두 감소시키는 효용을 이론적으로 증명한다. 적응성을 더 높이기 위해 이를 learnable orthogonal transformation으로 발전시킨다. Hadamard matrix로 초기화되고 Newton-Schulz iteration을 통해 orthogonality가 유지되는 이 모듈은 학습 중 다양한 입력 분포에 동적으로 적응한다. 대규모 language modeling 실험은 SmoothSpike가 information homogenization 문제를 효과적으로 완화하고 task performance를 향상시킴을 보여준다. 이는 SmoothSpike를 SNN과 ANN 사이의 성능 격차를 좁히는 robust한 해법으로 자리매김하게 한다.</p>"},{"id":"63061","en":"SMM Transformer: Leveraging Spiking Neural Networks for Multimodal Tasks","ko":"SMM Transformer: 멀티모달 태스크를 위한 Spiking Neural Network 활용","authors":"Xiubo Liang, Jinxing Han, Yuke Li, Haoqi Zhu, Yu Zhao, Hongzhi Wang","pos":"#316","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=aQmrtnFhqw","abs":"<p>Spiking Neural Networks (SNNs) enable event-driven computation with sparse activations, but building multimodal Transformers on SNNs is hindered by unstable training in deep spiking stacks and a mismatch between dense softmax attention and spike-based communication. We propose SMM Transformer, an SNN-based multimodal Transformer framework that combines (i) a Parallel LIF with Multistage Learnable Parameters (PLMP) neuron and a tailored P-STBP algorithm to stabilize training, (ii) a spike-driven attention approximation (SMSA) with a lightweight self-compensation branch, and (iii) a spiking mixture-of-experts (SMoE) module for modality-aware fusion. Across visual and multimodal benchmarks, SMM Transformer achieves competitive accuracy compared to ANN baselines while reducing the estimated compute energy of the attention module by up to 97\\% under a standard MAC/AC cost model.</p>","absKo":"<p>Spiking Neural Networks (SNNs)는 sparse activation을 이용한 event-driven computation을 가능하게 하지만, SNN 위에서 multimodal Transformer를 구축하는 일은 깊은 spiking stack에서의 불안정한 학습과 dense softmax attention과 spike 기반 communication 사이의 불일치 때문에 제약을 받는다. 우리는 SMM Transformer를 제안하는데, 이는 SNN 기반 multimodal Transformer 프레임워크로서 (i) 학습을 안정화하기 위한 Parallel LIF with Multistage Learnable Parameters (PLMP) neuron과 이에 맞춘 P-STBP algorithm, (ii) lightweight self-compensation branch를 갖는 spike-driven attention approximation (SMSA), (iii) modality-aware fusion을 위한 spiking mixture-of-experts (SMoE) module을 결합한다. 시각 및 multimodal benchmark 전반에서 SMM Transformer는 ANN baseline과 비교해 경쟁력 있는 정확도를 달성하면서, 표준 MAC/AC cost model 하에서 attention module의 추정 compute energy를 최대 97\\%까지 줄인다.</p>"},{"id":"62239","en":"AdaS: Adaptive Gradient Descent for Spiking Transformers","ko":"AdaS: Spiking Transformers를 위한 Adaptive Gradient Descent","authors":"Zijian Zhou, Honglin Cao, Ammar Belatreche, Wenjie Wei, Yimeng Shan, Yu Liang, Yu Yang, Shuai Wang, Yalan Ye, Malu Zhang, Yang Yang, Haizhou Li","pos":"#406","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=iQjyBjSDFp","abs":"<p>Transformer-based Spiking Neural Networks (SNNs) combine Transformer performance with SNN energy efficiency through an event-driven self-attention mechanism. However, Spiking Transformers still lag behind their Artificial Neural Network (ANN) counterparts. Most existing studies address this issue through new architectural designs, yet none has considered optimization algorithms specific to Spiking Transformers. Here, we first analyze the gradient characteristics of Spiking Transformers and identify excessive noise from surrogate gradient learning as a major challenge to stable training. We then provide a quantitative definition of noise in the gradient update direction and propose an adaptive gradient descent method for spiking transforms, named AdaS. Since moderate update direction noise can enhance generalization, whereas excessive noise degrades training, AdaS adaptively adjusts the update direction noise to an optimal level, thereby improving the performance of Spiking Transformers. We conduct extensive experiments on various Spiking Transformer architectures and datasets from both computer vision and natural language processing. The results demonstrate that the proposed AdaS consistently enhances performance across different Spiking Transformers, validating its effectiveness and generalizability. This work presents the first systematic investigation of optimization algorithms specifically tailored for SNNs, offering a practical tool to narrow the accuracy gap with ANNs while preserving the energy advantages of spike-based computation.</p>","absKo":"<p>Transformer-based Spiking Neural Network (SNN)은 event-driven self-attention mechanism을 통해 Transformer의 성능과 SNN의 에너지 효율을 결합한다. 그러나 Spiking Transformer는 여전히 Artificial Neural Network (ANN) 기반 대응 모델에 비해 뒤처진다. 기존 연구의 대부분은 새로운 architecture design으로 이 문제를 해결하지만, Spiking Transformer에 특화된 optimization algorithm은 고려하지 않았다. 여기서 우리는 먼저 Spiking Transformer의 gradient 특성을 분석하고, surrogate gradient learning에서 비롯되는 과도한 noise가 안정적인 training의 주요 문제임을 확인한다. 그런 다음 gradient update direction의 noise를 정량적으로 정의하고, AdaS라는 이름의 spiking transform용 adaptive gradient descent method를 제안한다. 적당한 update direction noise는 generalization을 향상시키는 반면, 과도한 noise는 training을 저해하므로, AdaS는 update direction noise를 최적 수준으로 적응적으로 조절하여 Spiking Transformer의 성능을 향상시킨다. 우리는 computer vision과 natural language processing 양쪽의 다양한 Spiking Transformer architecture와 dataset에 대해 광범위한 실험을 수행했다. 결과는 제안한 AdaS가 서로 다른 Spiking Transformer 전반에서 일관되게 성능을 향상시키며, 그 효과와 일반성을 검증함을 보여준다. 이 연구는 SNN에 특화된 optimization algorithm을 대상으로 한 최초의 체계적 조사로서, spike-based computation의 에너지 이점을 유지하면서 ANN과의 정확도 격차를 좁히기 위한 실용적 도구를 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"65031","en":"BIT-LLM: Brain Instruction Tuned LLM with persistent Cross-Attention for fMRI-to-Text Decoding","ko":"BIT-LLM: fMRI-to-Text Decoding을 위한 지속적 Cross-Attention 기반 Brain Instruction Tuned LLM","authors":"Sunghwan LEE, jihun kim, Chaelynn Kim, Jiyun Park, Jong-Hwan Lee","pos":"#407","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=HZhlRnJOHq","abs":"<p>Decoding fMRI into natural language is challenging because strong, pre-trained language priors can dominate autoregressive generation, obscuring whether a model truly utilizes neural evidence. We introduce BIT-LLM, which exposes fMRI-derived tokens as a persistent key–value memory through interleaved cross-attention adapters, enabling repeated neural access throughout decoding. BIT-LLM is trained with a three-stage pipeline: (i) multimodal contrastive learning to obtain semantically aligned fMRI representations, (ii) supervised fine-tuning to learn the brain-LLM interface while freezing the encoder and backbone LLM, and (iii) reward-based finetuning to optimize sequence-level caption quality directly. On the NSD subject-heldout benchmark (S1-7 train, S8 test), BIT-LLM yields substantially improved captioning quality over prior baselines under greedy decoding. In addition to standard captioning metrics, we perform several complementary evaluations to assess the robustness of brain–language grounding. Specifically, we conduct perturbation-based sanity checks by zeroing fMRI inputs or shuffling voxel values, and examine whether internal representations and generated outputs change accordingly. BIT-LLM exhibits clear sensitivity to these perturbations, indicating effective utilization of voxel values and their spatial correspondence.</p>"},{"id":"65137","en":"Bullet Trains: Parallelizing Training of Temporally Precise Spiking Neural Networks","ko":"Bullet Trains: 시간적으로 정밀한 Spiking Neural Network의 병렬 학습","authors":"Todd Morrill, Christian-Gernot Pehle, Anthony Zador","pos":"#408","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=GQIorrRZGv","abs":"<p>Continuous-time, event-native spiking neural networks (SNNs) operate strictly on spike events, treating spike timing and ordering as the representation rather than an artifact of time discretization. This viewpoint aligns with biological computation and with the native resolution of event sensors and neuromorphic processors, while enabling compute and memory that scale with the number of events. However, two challenges hinder practical, end-to-end trainable event-based SNN systems: 1) exact charge--fire--reset dynamics impose inherently sequential processing of input spikes, and 2) precise spike times must be solved without time bins. We address both. First, we use parallel associative scans to consume multiple input spikes at once, yielding up to 43x speedups over sequential simulation while retaining exact hard-reset dynamics. Second, we implement differentiable spike-time solvers that compute spike times to machine precision without discrete-time approximations or restrictive analytic assumptions. We demonstrate the viability of training SNNs using our solutions on four event-based datasets on GPUs.</p>"},{"id":"66489","en":"Efficiently Training Time-to-First-Spike Spiking Neural Networks from Scratch","ko":"무에서 Time-to-First-Spike Spiking Neural Network를 효율적으로 훈련하기","authors":"Kaiwei Che, Wei Fang, Zhengyu Ma, Yifan Huang, Peng Xue, Li Yuan, Yonghong Tian","pos":"#409","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=3EcT46wsdc","abs":"Spiking Neural Networks (SNNs), with their event-driven and biologically inspired mechanisms, are well-suited for energy-efficient neuromorphic hardware. Neural coding, which is critical to SNNs, determines how information is represented via spikes. While Time-to-First-Spike (TTFS) coding uses a single spike per neuron to offer extreme sparsity and energy efficiency, it often suffers from unstable training and low accuracy due to its sparse firing. To address these challenges, we propose a training framework that incorporates parameter initialization, training normalization, a temporal output decoder, and a re-evaluation of the pooling layer.  The proposed parameter initialization and training normalization mitigate signal diminishing and gradient vanishing, which helps stabilize training. Our output decoder aggregates temporal spikes to encourage earlier firing, thereby reducing latency. The re-evaluation of the pooling layer demonstrates that max-pooling violates single-spike constraints, which should be avoided, whereas average-pooling preserves them. Experiments show that our framework stabilizes and accelerates training, reduces latency, and achieves state-of-the-art accuracy for step-by-step TTFS SNNs on MNIST ($99.48\\%$), Fashion-MNIST ($92.90\\%$), CIFAR10 ($90.56\\%$), CIFAR100 ($70.27\\%$) and DVS Gesture ($95.83\\%$)."},{"id":"60660","en":"LIF Recurrent Memory Enables Long-Horizon Spiking Computation","ko":"LIF Recurrent Memory는 Long-Horizon Spiking Computation을 가능하게 한다","authors":"Fenghao Liu, Yipeng Shen, Peng Chen, Qian Zheng, Peng Lin, Gang Pan","pos":"#410","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=xwQytK4Yio","abs":"Processing long sequence data such as speech requires models to maintain long-term dependencies, which is challenging for recurrent spiking neural networks due to high temporal dynamics in neuron models that leak stored information in their membrane potentials, and due to vanishing gradients during backpropagation through time. These issues can be mitigated by employing more complex neuron designs, such as ALIF and TC-LIF, but these neuron-level solutions often incur high computational costs and complicate hardware implementation, undermining the efficiency advantages of Spiking neural networks. Here we propose an architectural-level solution that leverages the dynamical interactions of a few leaky integrate-and-fire (LIF) neurons to enhance long-term information storage. The memory capability of this LIF-based micro-circuit is adaptively modulated by global recurrent connections of the recurrent spiking neural network, contributing to selective enhancement of temporal information retention, and promoting stable gradient propagation through time. The proposed model outperforms previous methods including LSTM, ALIF, and TC-LIF in long sequence tasks, achieving 96.52\\% accuracy on the PS-MNIST dataset. Furthermore, our method also provides a compelling efficiency advantage, yielding up to 277$\\times$ computational efficiency improvement compared to conventional models such as LSTM. This work paves the way for building cost-effective, hardware-friendly, and interpretable spiking neural networks for long sequence modeling.","absKo":"처리해야 하는 speech와 같은 긴 sequence data는 모델이 장기 의존성을 유지해야 하며, 이는 recurrent spiking neural network에서 어렵다. 그 이유는 neuron model의 높은 temporal dynamics가 membrane potential에 저장된 정보를 누설하고, backpropagation through time 동안 vanishing gradient가 발생하기 때문이다. 이러한 문제는 ALIF와 TC-LIF와 같은 더 복잡한 neuron design을 사용하면 완화할 수 있지만, 이러한 neuron-level solution은 종종 높은 계산 비용을 초래하고 hardware implementation을 복잡하게 만들어, Spiking neural network의 효율성 이점을 훼손한다. 여기서 우리는 소수의 leaky integrate-and-fire(LIF) neuron의 dynamical interaction을 활용하여 장기 정보 저장을 향상시키는 architectural-level solution을 제안한다. 이 LIF-based micro-circuit의 memory capability는 recurrent spiking neural network의 전역 recurrent connection에 의해 적응적으로 조절되며, temporal information retention의 선택적 향상과 시간에 따른 안정적인 gradient propagation을 촉진한다. 제안 모델은 LSTM, ALIF, TC-LIF를 포함한 기존 방법을 긴 sequence task에서 능가하며, PS-MNIST dataset에서 96.52\\% accuracy를 달성한다. 더 나아가 본 방법은 LSTM과 같은 conventional model에 비해 최대 277$\\times$의 계산 효율 향상을 제공하는 강력한 효율성 이점도 보인다. 이 작업은 긴 sequence modeling을 위한 비용 효율적이고 hardware-friendly하며 해석 가능한 spiking neural network 구축의 길을 연다."},{"id":"62840","en":"MEG-XL: Data-Efficient Brain-to-Text via Long-Context Pre-Training","ko":"MEG-XL: Long-Context Pre-Training 기반 데이터 효율적인 Brain-to-Text","authors":"Dulhan Jayalath, ʻŌiwi Parker Jones","pos":"#411","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=cefix4VmhS","abs":"<p>Clinical brain-to-text interfaces are designed for paralysed patients who cannot provide extensive training recordings. Pre-training improves data-efficient generalisation by learning statistical priors across subjects, but these priors critically depend on context. While natural speech might unfold gradually over minutes, most methods pre-train with only a few seconds of context. Thus, we propose <em>MEG-XL</em>, a model pre-trained with 2.5 minutes of MEG context per sample, 5-300× longer than prior work, and equivalent to 191k tokens, capturing extended neural context. Fine-tuning on the task of word decoding from brain data, MEG-XL matches supervised performance with a fraction of the data (e.g. 1hr vs 50hrs) and outperforms brain foundation models. We find that models pre-trained with longer contexts learn representations that transfer better to word decoding. Our results indicate that long-context pre-training helps exploit extended neural context that other methods unnecessarily discard.</p>","absKo":"<p>임상용 brain-to-text interface는 대규모 training recording을 제공할 수 없는 마비 환자를 위해 설계된다. Pre-training은 subject 간 statistical prior를 학습함으로써 data-efficient generalisation을 향상시키지만, 이러한 prior는 context에 크게 의존한다. 자연어 speech는 수 분에 걸쳐 점진적으로 전개될 수 있지만, 대부분의 방법은 불과 몇 초의 context로 pre-training한다. 따라서 우리는 샘플당 2.5분의 MEG context로 pre-training된 <em>MEG-XL</em>을 제안한다. 이는 기존 연구보다 5-300배 길고 191k token에 해당하며, 확장된 neural context를 포착한다. brain data로부터의 word decoding task에 fine-tuning했을 때, MEG-XL은 훨씬 적은 data로 supervised 성능과 맞먹거나 이를 달성하며(예: 1시간 대 50시간), brain foundation model보다 우수한 성능을 보인다. 우리는 더 긴 context로 pre-training된 model이 word decoding으로 더 잘 전이되는 representation을 학습함을 발견했다. 우리의 결과는 long-context pre-training이 다른 방법들이 불필요하게 버리는 확장된 neural context를 활용하는 데 도움이 된다는 점을 시사한다.</p>"},{"id":"61451","en":"Practical Mechanism for Fault-Tolerant Spiking Neural Networks via Simple Input Control Based on Learnable Fragmentation","ko":"학습 가능한 Fragmentation 기반 단순 입력 제어를 통한 Fault-Tolerant Spiking Neural Networks의 실용적 메커니즘","authors":"Hyun-Jong Lee, Jae-Han Lim","pos":"#413","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=px1MlO0g26","abs":"<p>Spiking Neural Networks (SNNs) are regarded as the third generation of neural networks, offering energy-efficient computing for neuromorphic devices. Despite this benefit, hardware-implemented SNNs are vulnerable to hardware faults, which severely degrade their performance. Previous approaches have required direct access to internal SNN circuits to modify weights or monitor internal states, limiting their practicality. Improving robustness to hardware faults without such access remains challenging. To overcome this challenge, we propose a fault-tolerant mechanism that operates only through input data control. The hardware faults reduce the usable learning capacity of SNNs, leading to a mismatch between the instantaneous input load and the degraded network dynamics. Our mechanism mitigates this mismatch by dividing each input sample into multiple fragments, redistributing the input load via a learnable fragmentation strategy.  The strategy learns two key fragmentation components: 1) division boundaries and 2) the number of fragments. To our knowledge, this is the first to improve the fault tolerance of SNNs without accessing the internal SNN circuit. Experimental results demonstrate that our mechanism consistently outperforms previous methods in various SNN models, achieving these gains without direct access to internal circuits. Furthermore, we validate its effectiveness on SNNs implemented with a physical FPGA platform, confirming its practicality.</p>","absKo":"<p>Spiking Neural Networks (SNNs)는 신경형 컴퓨팅 장치를 위한 에너지 효율적인 계산을 제공하는, 신경망의 세 번째 세대로 여겨진다. 이러한 장점에도 불구하고, 하드웨어에 구현된 SNN은 hardware fault에 취약하여 성능이 크게 저하될 수 있다. 기존 접근법은 가중치를 수정하거나 내부 상태를 모니터링하기 위해 SNN의 내부 회로에 직접 접근해야 했기 때문에 실용성이 제한되었다. 이러한 접근 없이 hardware fault에 대한 robustness를 높이는 것은 여전히 어렵다. 이 문제를 극복하기 위해, 우리는 입력 데이터 제어만으로 동작하는 fault-tolerant 메커니즘을 제안한다. hardware fault는 SNN의 사용 가능한 학습 용량을 줄여, 순간적인 입력 부하와 저하된 network dynamics 사이에 불일치를 초래한다. 우리의 메커니즘은 각 입력 샘플을 여러 fragment로 분할하고, 학습 가능한 fragmentation 전략을 통해 입력 부하를 재분배함으로써 이 불일치를 완화한다. 이 전략은 두 가지 핵심 fragmentation 구성요소를 학습한다: 1) 분할 경계와 2) fragment의 개수. 우리가 아는 한, 이는 내부 SNN 회로에 접근하지 않고 SNN의 fault tolerance를 향상시키는 최초의 방법이다. 실험 결과는 우리의 메커니즘이 다양한 SNN 모델에서 이전 방법들을 일관되게 능가하며, 내부 회로에 직접 접근하지 않고도 이러한 성능 향상을 달성함을 보여준다. 또한 물리적 FPGA 플랫폼에서 구현된 SNN에 대해 그 효과를 검증하여, 실용성도 확인하였다.</p>"},{"id":"60483","en":"ROAMM: A Benchmark Dataset for Multimodal Human Attention Decoding and EEG-to-Text Modeling During Naturalistic Reading","ko":"ROAMM: 자연스러운 읽기 중 Multimodal Human Attention Decoding과 EEG-to-Text Modeling을 위한 Benchmark Dataset","authors":"Haorui Sun, Ardyn Olszko, Niharika Singh, David Jangraw","pos":"#414","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=zqLPdt09fE","abs":"<p>We present Reading Observed At Mindless Moments (ROAMM), a large-scale multimodal dataset comprising 50 hours of simultaneous EEG and eye-tracking recorded during naturalistic multi-page reading from 44 participants, with annotations including eye events, page-level comprehension scores, and word-level mind-wandering (MW) labels obtained via a retrospective self-report paradigm. We introduce a standardized evaluation protocol for MW detection under leave-one-subject-out evaluation, achieving up to 0.609 AUROC using supervised models. We also report results for EEG-to-text decoding trained on non-MW segments and show that decoding performance decreases when MW-labeled segments are included. Overall, ROAMM provides a benchmark dataset for MW detection and EEG-to-text decoding tasks, and enables the study of attention-related degradation in language decoding from brain activity in naturalistic reading.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 Reading Observed At Mindless Moments (ROAMM)을 제안한다. ROAMM은 44명의 참가자로부터 자연스러운 다중 페이지 읽기 동안 동시에 기록한 EEG와 eye-tracking 50시간 분량으로 구성된 대규모 multimodal dataset이며, retrospective self-report paradigm을 통해 얻은 eye events, page-level comprehension scores, word-level mind-wandering (MW) labels를 포함한 주석을 제공한다. 우리는 leave-one-subject-out evaluation 하에서 MW detection을 위한 표준화된 evaluation protocol을 제시하고, supervised models를 사용해 최대 0.609 AUROC를 달성함을 보인다. 또한 non-MW segments로 학습한 EEG-to-text decoding 결과를 보고하고, MW labeled segments를 포함하면 decoding performance가 감소함을 보인다. 전반적으로 ROAMM은 MW detection 및 EEG-to-text decoding tasks를 위한 benchmark dataset을 제공하며, 자연스러운 읽기에서 뇌 활동으로부터의 language decoding에서 attention 관련 degradation을 연구할 수 있게 한다.</p>"},{"id":"63746","en":"Resolving the Timestep Scaling Paradox in Spiking Neural Networks with a Timestep-Scalable Neuron Model","ko":"Timestep-S scalable Neuron Model로 Spiking Neural Networks의 timestep 스케일링 역설 해소","authors":"Binghao Ye, Wenjuan Li, Dengfeng Xue, Bing Li, Weiming Hu, Dong Liang, Kun Shang","pos":"#415","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=U63l7Uyeel","abs":"<p>Spiking Neural Networks (SNNs) have garnered increasing attention for their biological plausibility, energy efficiency, and temporal modeling capability. Due to the non-differentiability of spike generation, a widely used supervised training method for SNNs is backpropagation through time with surrogate gradients, which achieves competitive performance with a small number of timesteps. Intuitively, scaling timesteps should further improve performance by enriching temporal dynamics. However, we observe timestep scaling paradox (TSP), a counter-intuitive degradation in accuracy when scaling timesteps. We investigate TSP and link it to long-term temporal gradient vanishing and weakened cross-timestep dependencies. To address this, we propose the Timestep-Scalable (TS) neuron model. It introduces long-term memory reconsolidation to enhance cross-timestep information flow and enable effective learning with more timesteps. In parallel, a temporal forgetting mechanism periodically truncates the accumulation path, suppressing excessive temporal information buildup and improving training stability. Supported by theoretical analysis and extensive experiments, TS consistently improves performance when scaling timesteps. Beyond gains from timestep scaling, it attains state-of-the-art results on EEG signals, event-based recognition, and time-series forecasting, while remaining strong on conventional image classification and object detection datasets.</p>","absKo":"<p>Spiking Neural Networks(SNNs)는 생물학적 타당성, 에너지 효율성, temporal modeling capability 때문에 점점 더 주목받고 있다. spike 생성의 비미분성 때문에, SNN에서 널리 쓰이는 지도학습 방법은 surrogate gradient를 사용한 backpropagation through time이며, 이는 적은 timestep으로도 경쟁력 있는 성능을 달성한다. 직관적으로는 timestep을 늘리면 temporal dynamics가 풍부해져 성능이 더 좋아져야 한다. 그러나 우리는 timestep scaling paradox(TSP), 즉 timestep을 늘릴 때 정확도가 오히려 떨어지는 반직관적 저하를 관찰했다. 우리는 TSP를 조사하여 이를 장기 temporal gradient vanishing과 timestep 간 의존성 약화와 연결한다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 Timestep-Scalable(TS) neuron model을 제안한다. 이 모델은 long-term memory reconsolidation을 도입해 timestep 간 정보 흐름을 강화하고, 더 많은 timestep에서도 효과적인 학습을 가능하게 한다. 동시에 temporal forgetting mechanism은 accumulation path를 주기적으로 truncation하여 과도한 temporal information 축적을 억제하고 training stability를 향상시킨다. 이론적 분석과 광범위한 실험으로 뒷받침되는 TS는 timestep을 확장할 때 일관되게 성능을 향상시킨다. timestep scaling의 이득을 넘어 EEG signal, event-based recognition, time-series forecasting에서 state-of-the-art 결과를 달성하는 한편, 전통적인 image classification 및 object detection dataset에서도 강한 성능을 유지한다.</p>"},{"id":"65945","en":"Rethinking Attention in Spiking Transformers: Overcoming Density Bias with Set Similarity","ko":"Spiking Transformer에서의 Attention 재고: 집합 유사도로 밀도 편향 극복하기","authors":"JinGyo Lim, Seunggyu Jeong, Seong-Eun Kim","pos":"#416","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=8clCPAImE3","abs":"<p>Recent Spiking Transformer models have explored a variety of attention mechanisms beyond standard dot-product formulations. However, many existing similarity-based spiking attention formulations remain inherently sensitive to firing density, causing neurons with high spike rates to dominate attention scores regardless of semantic relevance. This density bias is particularly problematic in event-driven spiking representations, where sparse spike patterns often carry critical information. To address this limitation, we rethink spiking attention from a set-theoretic perspective. We propose DiceFormer, a novel Spiking Transformer architecture driven by Spike Dice Attention (SDA). Unlike traditional approaches, SDA replaces density-sensitive measures with a set similarity function derived from the Dice coefficient. By explicitly normalizing for firing density, SDA focuses on spike co-occurrence rather than high firing rates. We primarily evaluate DiceFormer on the challenging audio domain, where spike sparsity varies substantially across inputs. On AudioSet-20k, DiceFormer achieves a SOTA mAP of 0.161 with 54.3M parameters, outperforming prior SNN-based approaches and substantially narrowing the performance gap with ANN-based models. We also introduce Lin-SDA, a linearized version for computation efficiency, while achieving performance comparable to SDA. Beyond audio, we evaluate the effectiveness of SDA on CIFAR-100 to verify its applicability to the vision domain.</p>"},{"id":"60523","en":"NAACA: Training-Free NeuroAuditory Attentive Cognitive Architecture with Oscillatory Working Memory for Salience-Driven Attention Gating","ko":"NAACA: Salience-Driven Attention Gating을 위한 Oscillatory Working Memory 기반 Training-Free NeuroAuditory Attentive Cognitive Architecture","authors":"Zhongju Yuan, Geraint Wiggins, Dick Botteldooren","pos":"#710","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=zOWrIO6oKT","abs":"<p>Audio provides critical situational cues, yet current Audio Language Models (ALMs) face an attention bottleneck in long-form recordings where dominant background patterns can dilute rare, salient events. We introduce NAACA, a training-free NeuroAuditory Attentive Cognitive Architecture that reframes attention allocation as an auditory salience filtering problem. At its core is OWM, a neuro-inspired Oscillatory Working Memory that maintains stable attractor-like states and triggers higher-cognition ALM processing only when adaptive energy fluctuations signal perceptual salience, triggering higher-level reasoning. On XD-Violence, NAACA improves AudioQwen’s average precision (AP) from 53.50\\% to 70.60\\% while reducing unnecessary ALM invocations. Furthermore, qualitative case studies on the Urban Soundscapes of the World (USoW) dataset show that OWM captures novel events and subcategory shifts while remaining robust to transient pauses and ambient urban noise.</p>","absKo":"<p>Audio는 중요한 상황 단서를 제공하지만, 현재의 Audio Language Models (ALMs)는 장시간 녹음에서 attention bottleneck에 직면한다. 지배적인 배경 패턴이 드물지만 중요한 사건을 희석시킬 수 있기 때문이다. 우리는 attention allocation을 auditory salience filtering 문제로 재해석하는 training-free NeuroAuditory Attentive Cognitive Architecture인 NAACA를 제안한다. 그 핵심에는 OWM이 있는데, 이는 안정적인 attractor-like state를 유지하고 적응적 energy fluctuation이 perceptual salience를 신호할 때만 higher-cognition ALM 처리를 트리거하는 neuro-inspired Oscillatory Working Memory이며, 더 높은 수준의 추론을 유발한다. XD-Violence에서 NAACA는 AudioQwen의 average precision (AP)을 53.50\\%에서 70.60\\%로 향상시키는 동시에 불필요한 ALM 호출을 줄인다. 나아가 Urban Soundscapes of the World (USoW) 데이터셋에 대한 정성적 사례 연구는 OWM이 일시적 멈춤과 주변 도시 소음에도 견고하게 새로운 이벤트와 세부 하위 범주의 변화를 포착함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"61191","en":"DriveWorld-VLA: Unified Latent-Space World Modeling with Vision–Language–Action for Autonomous Driving","ko":"DriveWorld-VLA: 자율주행을 위한 Vision-Language-Action 기반 통합 잠재 공간 World Modeling","authors":"Feiyang Jia, Lin Liu, Ziying Song, Caiyan Jia, Hangjun Ye, Xiaoshuai Hao, Long Chen","pos":"#307","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=sseBmS2MGa","abs":"<p>End-to-end (E2E) autonomous driving has recently attracted increasing interest in unifying Vision–Language–Action (VLA) with World Models to enhance decision-making and forward-looking imagination. However, existing methods fail to effectively unify future scene evolution and action planning within a single architecture due to inadequate sharing of latent states, limiting the impact of visual imagination on action decisions. To address this limitation, we propose DriveWorld-VLA, a novel framework that unifies world modeling and planning within a latent space by tightly integrating VLA and world models at the representation level, which enables the VLA planner to benefit directly from holistic scene-evolution modeling and reducing reliance on dense annotated supervision. Additionally, DriveWorld-VLA incorporates the latent states of the world model as core decision-making states for the VLA planner, facilitating the planner to assess how candidate actions impact future scene evolution. By conducting world modeling entirely in the latent space, DriveWorld-VLA supports controllable, action-conditioned imagination at the feature level, avoiding expensive pixel-level rollouts. Extensive open-loop and closed-loop evaluations demonstrate the effectiveness of DriveWorld-VLA, which achieves state-of-the-art performance with 91.3 PDMS on NAVSIMv1, 86.8 EPDMS on NAVSIMv2, and 0.16 3-second average collision rate on nuScenes. Code and models will be publicly released.</p>","absKo":"<p>최근 end-to-end (E2E) autonomous driving에서는 의사결정과 미래 지향적 상상력을 강화하기 위해 Vision–Language–Action (VLA)와 World Models를 통합하려는 관심이 크게 높아지고 있다. 그러나 기존 방법들은 latent state의 공유가 충분하지 않아, 하나의 architecture 안에서 미래 scene evolution과 action planning을 효과적으로 통합하지 못하며, 이로 인해 시각적 상상력이 action decision에 미치는 영향도 제한된다. 이러한 한계를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 DriveWorld-VLA를 제안한다. 이는 representation level에서 VLA와 world models를 긴밀하게 통합함으로써 latent space 내에서 world modeling과 planning을 하나로 묶는 새로운 framework이며, VLA planner가 holistic한 scene-evolution modeling의 이점을 직접 누리고 dense annotated supervision에 대한 의존도를 줄이도록 한다. 또한 DriveWorld-VLA는 world model의 latent states를 VLA planner의 핵심 decision-making state로 통합하여, 후보 action이 미래 scene evolution에 어떤 영향을 미치는지 planner가 평가할 수 있게 한다. world modeling을 전적으로 latent space에서 수행함으로써, DriveWorld-VLA는 feature level에서 controllable한 action-conditioned imagination을 지원하고, 비용이 큰 pixel-level rollout을 피한다. 광범위한 open-loop 및 closed-loop 평가 결과는 DriveWorld-VLA의 효과를 입증하며, NAVSIMv1에서 91.3 PDMS, NAVSIMv2에서 86.8 EPDMS, nuScenes에서 3초 평균 collision rate 0.16으로 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성한다. 코드와 모델은 공개될 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"65414","en":"PATRA: Pattern-Aware Alignment and Balanced Reasoning for Time Series Question Answering","ko":"PATRA: 시계열 질의응답을 위한 패턴 인지 정합 및 균형 추론","authors":"Junkai Lu, Peng Chen, Xingjian Wu, Yang Shu, Chenjuan Guo, Christian S Jensen, Bin Yang","pos":"#202","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Du8BMHfNzp","abs":"<p>Time series reasoning demands both the perception of complex dynamics and logical depth. However, existing LLM-based approaches exhibit two limitations: they often treat time series merely as text or images, failing to capture the patterns like trends and seasonalities needed to answer specific questions; and when trained on a mix of simple and complex tasks, simpler objectives often dominate the learning process, hindering the development of deep reasoning capabilities. To address these limitations, we propose the Pattern-Aware Alignment and Balanced Reasoning model (PATRA), introducing a pattern-aware mechanism that extracts trend and seasonality patterns from time series to achieve deep alignment. Furthermore, we design a task-aware balanced reward to harmonize learning across tasks of varying difficulty, incentivizing the generation of coherent Chains of Thought. Extensive experiments show that PATRA outperforms strong baselines across diverse Time Series Question Answering (TSQA) tasks, demonstrating superior cross-modal understanding and reasoning capability.</p>"},{"id":"65709","en":"A Very Big Video Reasoning Suite","ko":"아주 큰 영상 추론 스위트","authors":"Maijunxian Wang, Ruisi Wang, Juyi Lin, Ran Ji, Thaddäus Wiedemer, Qingying Gao, Dezhi Luo, Yaoyao Qian, Lianyu Huang, Zelong Hong, Jiahui Ge, Qianli Ma, Hang He, Yifan Zhou, Lingzi Guo, Lantao Mei, Jiachen Li, Hanwen Xing, Tianqi Zhao, Fengyuan Yu, Weihang Xiao, Yizheng Jiao, Jianheng Hou, Danyang Zhang, Pengcheng Xu, Boyang ZHONG, Zehong Zhao, Gaoyun Fang, John Kitaoka, Xu Yile, Hua XU, Kenton Blacutt, Tin Nguyen, Siyuan Song, Haoran Sun, shaoyue wen, Linyang He, Runming Wang, Yanzhi Wang, Mengyue Yang, Ziqiao Ma, Raphaël Millière, Freda Shi, Nuno Vasconcelos, Daniel Khashabi, Alan Yuille, Yilun Du, Ziming Liu, Dahua Lin, Ziwei Liu, Vikash Kumar, Yijiang Li, Lei Yang, Zhongang Cai, Hokin Deng","pos":"#1108","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=AwC77yHpP6","abs":"<p>Video reasoning grounds intelligence in spatiotemporally consistent visual environments that go beyond what text can naturally capture, enabling intuitive reasoning over motion, interaction, and causality. Rapid progress in video models has focused primarily on visual quality. Systematically studying video reasoning and its scaling behavior suffers from a lack of video reasoning (training) data. To address this gap, we introduce the Very Big Video Reasoning (VBVR) Dataset, an unprecedentedly large-scale resource spanning 200 curated reasoning tasks and over one million video clips—approximately three orders of magnitude larger than existing datasets. We further present VBVR-Bench, a verifiable evaluation framework that moves beyond model-based judging by incorporating rule-based, human-aligned scorers, enabling reproducible and interpretable diagnosis of video reasoning capabilities. Leveraging the VBVR suite, we conduct one of the first large-scale scaling studies of video reasoning and observe early signs of emergent generalization to unseen reasoning tasks. Together, VBVR lays a foundation for the next stage of research in generalizable video reasoning. The data, toolkit, and models will be released publicly.</p>"},{"id":"60506","en":"Towards Spectroscopy: Susceptibility Clusters in Language Models","ko":"Spectroscopy를 향하여: Language Model의 Susceptibility Cluster","authors":"Andrew Gordon, Daniel Murfet, William Snell, Garrett Baker, George Wang, Stan van Wingerden","pos":"#107","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=zYSl5Qj6Cw","abs":"Spectroscopy infers the internal structure of physical systems by measuring their response to perturbations. We apply this principle to neural networks: perturbing the data distribution by upweighting a token $y$ in context $x$, we measure the model's response via susceptibilities $\\chi_{xy}$, which are covariances between component-level observables and the perturbation computed over a localized Gibbs posterior via stochastic gradient Langevin dynamics (SGLD). Theoretically, we show that susceptibilities decompose as a sum over \\emph{modes} of the data distribution, explaining why tokens that follow their contexts ``for similar reasons'' cluster together in susceptibility space. Empirically, we apply this methodology to Pythia-14M, developing a conductance-based clustering algorithm that identifies 510 interpretable clusters ranging from grammatical patterns to code structure to mathematical notation. Comparing to sparse autoencoders, 50\\% of our clusters match SAE features, validating that both methods recover similar structure.","absKo":"분광법(spectroscopy)은 물리 시스템의 internal structure를 perturbation에 대한 응답을 측정함으로써 추론한다. 우리는 이 원리를 neural network에 적용한다. context x에서 token y의 가중치를 높여 data distribution을 perturbing하고, 우리는 SGLD(stochastic gradient Langevin dynamics)를 통해 계산한 localized Gibbs posterior에서 component-level observable과 perturbation 사이의 covariance인 susceptibility \\chi_{xy}를 통해 모델의 응답을 측정한다. 이론적으로, 우리는 susceptibility가 data distribution의 \\emph{mode}들의 합으로 분해됨을 보이며, 왜 context를 ``비슷한 이유로'' 따르는 token들이 susceptibility space에서 함께 군집하는지를 설명한다. 실험적으로, 우리는 이 방법론을 Pythia-14M에 적용하고, grammatical pattern에서 code structure, mathematical notation에 이르기까지 510개의 해석 가능한 cluster를 식별하는 conductance-based clustering algorithm을 개발한다. sparse autoencoder와 비교했을 때, 우리의 cluster 중 50\\%가 SAE feature와 일치하여, 두 방법이 유사한 구조를 복원함을 검증한다."},{"id":"60481","en":"Why Specialist Models Still Matter: A Heterogeneous Multi-Agent Paradigm for Medical Artificial Intelligence","ko":"왜 Specialist Model은 여전히 중요한가: 의료 AI를 위한 이질적 Multi-Agent 패러다임","authors":"Yanan Wang, Shuaicong Hu, Jian Liu, Guohui Zhou, Aiguo Wang, Cuiwei Yang","pos":"#115","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=zrVSSx6348","abs":"<p>The impressive performance of generalist large language models (LLMs) such as GPT-4 and Claude in healthcare raises a critical question: will domain-specific medical specialist models become obsolete? We argue that the future of medical artificial intelligence (AI) lies not in building monolithic medical foundation models, nor in replacing human expertise, but in orchestrating collaboration among generalist LLMs, domain-specific specialist models, and clinicians. We propose HetMedAgent, a heterogeneous medical multi-agent framework that enables conflict-aware evidence fusion, uncertainty-based clinician intervention triggering, and adaptive threshold calibration. Experiments on three real-world clinical decision-making tasks demonstrate that the synergy between generalist LLMs and domain-specific specialist models significantly outperforms using either type of model alone, validating the irreplaceable value of specialist models in modality-specific analysis. HetMedAgent drives a paradigm shift from building medical LLMs or foundation models to multi-agent collaboration, achieving a balance between general reasoning capabilities and domain-specific precision.</p>","absKo":"<p>GPT-4와 Claude 같은 generalist large language model (LLM)의 healthcare에서의 인상적인 성능은 중요한 질문을 제기한다. domain-specific medical specialist model은 결국 쓸모없어질 것인가? 우리는 의료 artificial intelligence (AI)의 미래가 단일한 medical foundation model을 구축하거나 인간의 전문성을 대체하는 데 있는 것이 아니라, generalist LLM, domain-specific specialist model, clinician 간의 협업을 조율하는 데 있다고 주장한다. 우리는 conflict-aware evidence fusion, uncertainty-based clinician intervention triggering, adaptive threshold calibration을 가능하게 하는 heterogeneous medical multi-agent framework인 HetMedAgent를 제안한다. 세 가지 실제 clinical decision-making task에 대한 실험은 generalist LLM과 domain-specific specialist model의 시너지가 두 종류의 모델 중 어느 하나만 사용하는 것보다 훨씬 우수함을 보여주며, modality-specific analysis에서 specialist model이 대체 불가능하다는 가치를 검증한다. HetMedAgent는 medical LLM이나 foundation model을 구축하는 패러다임에서 multi-agent collaboration으로의 전환을 이끌며, general reasoning capability와 domain-specific precision 사이의 균형을 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"63963","en":"Deep Single-Index Fréchet Regression","ko":"Deep Single-Index Fréchet 회귀","authors":"MUQING CUI, Yidong Zhou, Su Iao, Hans-Georg Müller","pos":"#1314","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=SCjiMmzyFA","abs":"<p>Predicting outputs that are located in non-Euclidean spaces, such as probability distributions, networks, and symmetric positive-definite matrices, is becoming increasingly important in modern data analysis, particularly when inputs are high-dimensional. We propose DeSI (Deep Single-Index Fréchet Regression), a semiparametric framework for regression with metric space-valued outputs and multivariate inputs that assumes a single-index structure for the conditional Fréchet mean. DeSI estimates an interpretable index direction, which quantifies the relative importance of inputs, using a deep neural network, and performs Fréchet regression along the resulting one-dimensional index in the target metric space. This structure mitigates the curse of dimensionality while retaining interpretability, which stands in contrast to standard deep neural networks. We establish theoretical guarantees for DeSI, including consistency and convergence rates, and demonstrate its strong predictive performance through simulations on distributions, networks, and symmetric positive-definite matrices, as well as an application to compositional mood data from New Jersey.</p>","absKo":"<p>probability distribution, network, symmetric positive-definite matrix와 같은 비유클리드 공간에 위치한 output을 예측하는 일은 현대 데이터 분석에서 점점 더 중요해지고 있으며, 특히 input이 고차원일 때 더욱 그렇다. 우리는 metric space-valued output과 multivariate input에 대한 regression을 위한 semiparametric framework인 DeSI(Deep Single-Index Fréchet Regression)를 제안한다. 이 방법은 conditional Fréchet mean에 대해 single-index 구조를 가정한다. DeSI는 deep neural network를 사용해 입력들의 상대적 중요도를 정량화하는 interpretable한 index direction을 추정하고, 이를 바탕으로 target metric space에서 생성되는 1차원 index를 따라 Fréchet regression을 수행한다. 이러한 구조는 표준 deep neural network와 달리 해석 가능성을 유지하면서도 curse of dimensionality를 완화한다. 우리는 DeSI에 대해 consistency와 convergence rate를 포함한 이론적 보장을 확립하고, distribution, network, symmetric positive-definite matrix에 대한 simulation과 New Jersey의 compositional mood data 적용을 통해 강한 예측 성능을 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"64299","en":"TrustworthyQENN: A Quantum Evidential Neural Network Based on Complex-Valued Contrastive Learning for Uncertainty Pattern Classification","ko":"TrustworthyQENN: 불확실성 패턴 분류를 위한 복소값 대조 학습 기반 양자 증거 신경망","authors":"Xiaolong Chen, Fuyuan Xiao, Xiaohong Zhang, Zehong Cao, Chin-teng Lin","pos":"#1508","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=P0d4D0AGza","abs":"<p>Out-of-Distribution (OOD) detection requires accurately classifying In-Distribution (ID) samples while effectively distinguishing anomalous OOD data. However, existing methodologies predominantly rely on real-valued magnitude features, neglecting the semantic richness embedded in phase information, and often lack a systematic theoretical framework for quantitively modeling uncertainty. To address this dual limitation of incomplete feature representation and insufficient uncertainty modeling, the Trustworthy Quantum Evidence Neural Network (TrustworthyQENN) is proposed, a novel framework bridging complex-valued representation learning with Generalized Quantum Evidence Theory (GQET). Specifically, Supervised Complex-Valued Contrastive Learning (SCVCL) is proposed to synchronize amplitude distributions with phase correlations, thereby enforcing high intra-class compactness and inter-class separability for ID data. A quantum evidence generation mechanism based on GQET is subsequently devised, where the OOD state is formally grounded as the quantum empty set within a Hilbert space. Furthermore, the Generalized Quantum Evidential Combination Rule (GQECR) is leveraged to fuse multi-view evidence, thereby achieving trustworthy inference. Extensive experiments on the MSTAR, EuroSAT, and FUSAR-Ship benchmarks substantiate the superiority of TrustworthyQENN, which achieves a peak AUROC of 95.94% on the MSTAR dataset while consistently outperforming state-of-the-art methods across all evaluated scenarios.</p>","absKo":"<p>Out-of-Distribution(OOD) detection은 In-Distribution(ID) sample을 정확하게 분류하는 동시에 이상 OOD 데이터를 효과적으로 구별해야 한다. 그러나 기존 방법론은 주로 실수값 magnitude feature에 의존하여 phase information에 담긴 semantic richness를 간과하며, uncertainty를 정량적으로 모델링하기 위한 체계적인 이론적 프레임워크도 부족한 경우가 많다. 이러한 불완전한 feature 표현과 불충분한 uncertainty modeling이라는 이중 한계를 해결하기 위해, complex-valued representation learning과 Generalized Quantum Evidence Theory(GQET)를 연결하는 새로운 프레임워크인 Trustworthy Quantum Evidence Neural Network(TrustworthyQENN)를 제안한다. 구체적으로, Supervised Complex-Valued Contrastive Learning(SCVCL)을 제안하여 amplitude distribution과 phase correlation을 동기화함으로써 ID data에 대해 높은 intra-class compactness와 inter-class separability를 강제한다. 이후 GQET에 기반한 quantum evidence 생성 메커니즘을 고안하는데, 여기서 OOD state는 Hilbert space 내의 quantum empty set으로 정식화된다. 또한 Generalized Quantum Evidential Combination Rule(GQECR)을 활용하여 multi-view evidence를 융합함으로써 trustworthy inference를 달성한다. MSTAR, EuroSAT, FUSAR-Ship benchmark에 대한 광범위한 실험은 TrustworthyQENN의 우수성을 입증하며, TrustworthyQENN은 MSTAR dataset에서 95.94%의 peak AUROC를 달성하는 동시에 평가한 모든 시나리오에서 state-of-the-art 방법들을 일관되게 능가한다.</p>"},{"id":"64904","en":"Temporal Straightening for Latent Planning","ko":"Latent Planning을 위한 시간적 정렬화","authors":"Ying Wang, Oumayma Bounou, Gaoyue Zhou, Randall Balestriero, Tim G. J. Rudner, Yann LeCun, Mengye Ren","pos":"#1509","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Ik1mKtUYlZ","abs":"<p>Learning good representations is essential for latent planning with world models. While pretrained visual encoders provide strong visual features, they are not tailored to planning and contain substantial information which is irrelevant to planning. Inspired by the perceptual straightening hypothesis in human visual processing, we introduce temporal straightening for representation learning in latent planning. We add a lightweight projector on top of a pretrained visual encoder to map to a lower-dimensional space, trained with a curvature regularizer that encourages locally straightened latent trajectories. We show that reducing curvature improves the conditioning of the planning objective, making gradient-based planning more stable and yielding significantly higher success rates across four goal-reaching tasks.</p>"},{"id":"62495","en":"Seeing to Generalize: How Visual Data Corrects Binding Shortcuts","ko":"일반화를 위한 보기: 시각 데이터가 binding shortcut을 바로잡는 방식","authors":"Nicolas Buzeta, Felipe del Rio, Cristian Hinostroza, Denis Parra, Hans Lobel, Rodrigo Toro Icarte","pos":"#1710","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=g6wvLLdH1l","abs":"<p>Vision Language Models (VLMs) are designed to extend Large Language Models (LLMs) with visual capabilities, yet in this work we observe a surprising phenomenon: VLMs can outperform their underlying LLMs on purely text-only tasks, particularly in long-context information retrieval. To investigate this effect, we build a controlled synthetic retrieval task and find that a transformer trained only on text achieves perfect in-distribution accuracy but fails to generalize out of distribution, while subsequent training on an image-tokenized version of the same task nearly doubles text-only OOD performance. Mechanistic interpretability reveals that visual training changes the model’s internal binding strategy: text-only training encourages positional shortcuts, whereas image-based training disrupts them through spatial translation invariance, forcing the model to adopt a more robust symbolic binding mechanism that persists even after text-only examples are reintroduced. We further characterize how binding strategies vary across training regimes, visual encoders, and initializations, and show that analogous shifts occur during pretrained LLM-to-VLM transitions. Our findings suggest that cross‑modal training can enhance reasoning and generalization even for tasks grounded in a single modality.</p>","absKo":"<p>Vision Language Models (VLMs)는 Large Language Models (LLMs)에 visual capability를 확장하도록 설계되었지만, 본 연구에서는 놀라운 현상을 관찰한다. VLM이 기반이 되는 LLM보다 순수 텍스트-only task, 특히 long-context information retrieval에서 더 나은 성능을 보일 수 있다는 점이다. 이 효과를 조사하기 위해 통제된 synthetic retrieval task를 구축했으며, text로만 학습한 transformer는 in-distribution accuracy는 완벽하지만 out-of-distribution 일반화에는 실패하는 반면, 같은 task의 image-tokenized version으로 추가 학습하면 text-only OOD 성능이 거의 두 배 향상된다는 것을 발견했다. Mechanistic interpretability 분석은 visual training이 model 내부의 binding strategy를 바꾼다는 점을 보여준다. text-only training은 positional shortcut을 장려하는 반면, image-based training은 spatial translation invariance를 통해 이를 방해하여, model이 더 강건한 symbolic binding mechanism을 채택하도록 만든다. 이 메커니즘은 이후 text-only example을 다시 도입한 뒤에도 유지된다. 우리는 또한 training regime, visual encoder, initialization에 따라 binding strategy가 어떻게 달라지는지 더 자세히 특성화하고, 유사한 변화가 pretrained LLM에서 VLM으로 전이되는 과정에서도 발생함을 보인다. 이러한 결과는 cross-modal training이 단일 modality에 기반한 task에서도 reasoning과 generalization을 향상시킬 수 있음을 시사한다.</p>"},{"id":"66784","en":"Procedural Generation Of Algorithm Discovery Tasks in Machine Learning","ko":"기계 학습에서 알고리즘 발견 태스크의 절차적 생성","authors":"Alexander D. Goldie, Zilin Wang, Adrian Hayler, Deepak Nathani, Edan Toledo, Aleksandra Kalisz, Ken Thampiratwong, Michael Beukman, Alistair Letcher, Shashank Reddy Chirra, Clarisse Wibault, Theo Wolf, Charles O&amp;#x27;Neill, Uljad Berdica, Nicholas Roberts, Saeed Rahmani, Roberta Raileanu, Shimon Whiteson, Jakob Foerster","pos":"#1803","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=0Mvm3lqLjF","abs":"<p>Automating the development of machine learning algorithms has the potential to unlock new breakthroughs. However, our ability to improve and evaluate algorithm discovery systems has thus far been limited by existing task suites. They suffer from many issues, such as: poor evaluation methodologies; data contamination; and containing saturated or very similar problems. Here, we introduce <em>DiscoGen</em>, a procedural generator of algorithm discovery tasks for machine learning, such as developing optimisers for reinforcement learning or loss functions for image classification. Motivated by the success of procedural generation in reinforcement learning, DiscoGen spans millions of tasks of varying difficulty and complexity from a range of machine learning fields. These tasks are specified by a small number of configuration parameters and can be used to optimise algorithm discovery agents (ADAs). We present <em>DiscoBench</em>, a benchmark consisting of a fixed, small subset of DiscoGen tasks for principled evaluation of ADAs. Finally, we propose a number of ambitious, impactful research directions enabled by DiscoGen, in addition to experiments demonstrating its use for prompt optimisation of an ADA. DiscoGen is released open-source.</p>"},{"id":"64601","en":"Random Scaling of Emergence Capabilities","ko":"Emergence 능력의 무작위 Scaling","authors":"Rosie Zhao, Tian Qin, David Alvarez-Melis, Sham Kakade, Naomi Saphra","pos":"#1811","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Lp8gwhhUfU","abs":"<p>Language models famously improve under a smooth scaling law, but some specific capabilities exhibit sudden breakthroughs in performance. Advocates of \"emergence\" view breakthroughs as unlocked capabilities, but others attribute them to metric thresholding effects. We propose that breakthroughs are instead driven by continuous changes in the <em>probability distribution</em> of training outcomes when performance is bimodally distributed across random seeds. we show that different random seeds can produce <em>either</em> smooth <em>or</em> emergent scaling trends in synthetic length generalization tasks, multiple choice question answering, and grammatical generalization. We reveal that sharp breakthroughs in metrics are produced by underlying continuous changes in their distribution across seeds.</p>","absKo":"<p>Language model은 매끄러운 scaling law에 따라 유명하게 성능이 향상되지만, 특정 capability는 성능에서 갑작스러운 돌파를 보이기도 한다. \"emergence\" 지지자들은 이러한 돌파를 새롭게 풀리는 capability로 해석하지만, 다른 이들은 이를 metric thresholding 효과로 본다. 우리는 이러한 돌파가 무작위 seed 전반에서 performance가 bimodally 분포할 때 training outcome의 <em>probability distribution</em>에 일어나는 연속적인 변화에 의해 유도된다고 제안한다. 우리는 synthetic length generalization task, multiple choice question answering, 그리고 grammatical generalization에서 서로 다른 random seed가 <em>smooth</em>한 scaling trend 또는 <em>emergent</em> scaling trend 중 <em>어느 하나</em>를 만들어낼 수 있음을 보인다. 우리는 metric에서의 급격한 돌파가 seed 전반의 분포에서 일어나는 근본적인 연속적 변화에 의해 생성됨을 밝힌다.</p>"},{"id":"64731","en":"JADE: Bridging the Strategic-Operational Gap in Dynamic Agentic RAG","ko":"JADE: 동적 Agentic RAG에서 전략-운영 간극 연결","authors":"Yiqun Chen, Erhan Zhang, Tianyi Hu, Shijie Wang, Zixuan Yang, Meizhi Zhong, Xiaochi Wei, Yan Gao, YIWU, Yao Hu, Jiaxin Mao","pos":"#2008","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=KQT6pf4Mva","abs":"<p>The evolution of Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) has shifted from static retrieval pipelines to dynamic, agentic workflows where a central planner orchestrates multi-turn reasoning. However, existing paradigms face a critical dichotomy: they either optimize modules jointly within rigid, fixed-graph architectures, or empower dynamic planning while treating executors as frozen, black-box tools. We identify that this \\textit{decoupled optimization} creates a ``strategic-operational mismatch,'' where sophisticated planning strategies fail to materialize due to unadapted local executors, often leading to negative performance gains despite increased system complexity. In this paper, we propose \\textbf{JADE} (\\textbf{J}oint \\textbf{A}gentic \\textbf{D}ynamic \\textbf{E}xecution), a unified framework for the joint optimization of planning and execution within dynamic, multi-turn workflows. By modeling the system as a cooperative multi-agent team unified under a single shared backbone, JADE enables end-to-end learning driven by outcome-based rewards. This approach facilitates \\textit{co-adaptation}: the planner learns to operate within the capability boundaries of the executors, while the executors evolve to align with high-level strategic intent. Empirical results demonstrate that JADE transforms disjoint modules into a synergistic system, yielding remarkable performance improvements via joint optimization and enabling a flexible balance between efficiency and effectiveness through dynamic workflow orchestration.</p>","absKo":"<p>Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)의 발전은 정적 retrieval pipeline에서 중앙 planner가 multi-turn reasoning을 조율하는 동적이고 agentic한 workflow로 이동해 왔다. 그러나 기존 패러다임은 중대한 이분법에 직면한다. 즉, 하나는 rigid한 fixed-graph architecture 안에서 module들을 공동으로 최적화하고, 다른 하나는 dynamic planning을 가능하게 하되 executor를 고정된 black-box tool로 취급한다. 우리는 이러한 \\textit{decoupled optimization}이 “strategic-operational mismatch”를 만들어낸다고 지적한다. 즉, local executor가 적응하지 못한 채로는 정교한 planning strategy가 실제로 구현되지 못하며, 이는 종종 시스템 복잡성은 증가하지만 성능 향상은 오히려 음수에 가까워지는 결과로 이어진다. 본 논문에서는 dynamic multi-turn workflow 내에서 planning과 execution을 공동 최적화하기 위한 통합 프레임워크인 \\textbf{JADE}(\\textbf{J}oint \\textbf{A}gentic \\textbf{D}ynamic \\textbf{E}xecution)를 제안한다. 하나의 공유 backbone 아래 통합된 cooperative multi-agent team으로 시스템을 모델링함으로써, JADE는 outcome-based reward에 의해 구동되는 end-to-end learning을 가능하게 한다. 이 접근은 \\textit{co-adaptation}을 촉진한다. 즉, planner는 executor의 capability boundary 내에서 동작하는 법을 학습하고, executor는 높은 수준의 strategic intent에 맞게 진화한다. 실험 결과는 JADE가 서로 분리된 module들을 시너지 효과를 내는 시스템으로 전환하며, joint optimization을 통해 현저한 성능 향상을 달성하고, dynamic workflow orchestration을 통해 효율성과 효과성 사이의 유연한 균형을 가능하게 함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"63640","en":"Large Language Models as Topological Thinkers: A Benchmark on Graph Persistent Homology","ko":"대형 언어 모델을 위상적 사고자로 보기: 그래프 persistent homology 벤치마크","authors":"Hao Li, Hao Wan, Yixue Huang, Yuzhou Chen, Yulia Gel, Hao Jiang","pos":"#2012","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=V7gjpaYyI1","abs":"<p>Large language models (LLMs) are increasingly used in scientific discovery, system modeling, and decision-making, prompting interest in their ability to reason over complex structured data. Existing benchmarks primarily focus on static or local graph reasoning, overlooking the high-order structures in real-world systems whose global properties evolve across multiple scales. We introduce LLM4PH, a benchmark that evaluates multi-scale structural reasoning through the lens of persistent homology (PH), a topological framework for tracking structural evolution. LLM4PH decomposes the PH pipeline into interpretable reasoning tasks spanning synthetic and real-world graphs, revealing that most models struggle with reasoning over structural transitions and persistence. Beyond task-level evaluation, we perform cross-task ablations on prompt encoding and transfer, explore post-training effects, and construct a compositional PH pipeline to assess end-to-end performance. Our results provide the first in-depth view of how well LLMs bridge discrete graph structures with continuous topological abstraction, and offer insights into their potential for structure-aware scientific reasoning.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large language models(LLMs)는 과학적 발견, 시스템 모델링, 의사결정에 점점 더 많이 사용되고 있으며, 이에 따라 복잡한 구조화된 데이터를 추론하는 능력에 대한 관심도 커지고 있다. 기존 benchmark는 주로 static하거나 local한 graph reasoning에 초점을 맞추어, 전역적 특성이 여러 scale에 걸쳐 진화하는 실제 시스템의 high-order structure를 간과한다. 우리는 LLM4PH를 소개한다. 이는 structural evolution을 추적하는 topological framework인 persistent homology(PH)의 관점에서 multi-scale structural reasoning을 평가하는 benchmark이다. LLM4PH는 PH pipeline을 synthetic graph와 real-world graph 전반에 걸친 해석 가능한 reasoning task로 분해하며, 대부분의 model이 structural transition과 persistence에 대한 추론에 어려움을 겪는다는 점을 드러낸다. task-level 평가를 넘어, prompt encoding과 transfer에 대한 cross-task ablation을 수행하고, post-training 효과를 탐구하며, end-to-end 성능을 평가하기 위한 compositional PH pipeline을 구성한다. 우리의 결과는 LLM이 discrete graph structure와 continuous topological abstraction 사이를 얼마나 잘 연결하는지에 대한 첫 심층 관점을 제공하며, structure-aware scientific reasoning에 대한 잠재력에 관한 통찰을 제시한다.</p>"},{"id":"62363","en":"Learning Multi-Agent Coordination via Sheaf-ADMM","ko":"Sheaf-ADMM을 통한 다중 에이전트 협업 학습","authors":"Jeffrey Seely, Bartłomiej Cupiał, Llion Jones","pos":"#2414","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=hGeKiXnUIT","abs":"<p>We present a differentiable optimization framework for multi-agent coordination. An input is decomposed into overlapping local views, each processed by an agent that solves a convex subproblem parametrized by a neural encoder. Agents coordinate through the Alternating Direction Method of Multipliers (ADMM) with inter-agent constraints specified by a cellular sheaf. The sheaf specifies which aspects of neighboring solutions must agree. Backpropagating through the unrolled optimization jointly trains encoders, decoders, and sheaf structure. We evaluate on maze pathfinding, image classification, and Sudoku, where agents with individually insufficient local views coordinate to produce correct global outputs. We show that this locality also yields improved robustness to distribution shifts (padding, missing patches, and noise) when evaluated against a standard CNN on MNIST, while exposing interpretable primal/consensus/dual variables that make the coordination dynamics directly inspectable.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 multi-agent coordination을 위한 미분 가능한 optimization framework를 제시한다. 입력은 중첩되는 local view들로 분해되며, 각 view는 neural encoder로 매개변수화된 convex subproblem을 푸는 agent에 의해 처리된다. agent들은 cellular sheaf로 지정된 inter-agent constraint를 갖는 Alternating Direction Method of Multipliers (ADMM)을 통해 협력한다. sheaf는 이웃 solution의 어떤 측면이 일치해야 하는지를 규정한다. 전개(unrolled)된 optimization을 통한 backpropagation은 encoder, decoder, 그리고 sheaf structure를 공동으로 학습한다. 우리는 maze pathfinding, image classification, Sudoku에서 평가하며, 개별적으로는 충분하지 않은 local view를 가진 agent들이 협력하여 올바른 global output을 만들어냄을 보인다. 또한 MNIST에서 표준 CNN과 비교했을 때, 이러한 locality가 distribution shift(padding, missing patch, noise)에 대한 robustness를 향상시킴을 보이며, 직관적으로 검토 가능한 primal/consensus/dual 변수를 노출하여 coordination dynamics를 직접 관찰할 수 있게 한다.</p>"},{"id":"61575","en":"Set-Coupled Guidance: Set-Level Coordination in Diffusion-Based Dataset Distillation","ko":"Set-Coupled Guidance: Diffusion-Based Dataset Distillation에서 Set-Level Coordination","authors":"Ziang Gan, Qi Zhu, Libao Zhang","pos":"#2505","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=onosLtwoiK","abs":"<p>Diffusion models serve as generative priors for dataset distillation, yet existing pipelines rely on per-sample update rules that evolve each synthetic image independently, limiting their ability to optimize collective set-level objectives. We propose Set-Coupled Guidance (SCG), a plug-and-play auxiliary controller that shifts from per-image to group (IPC-at-once) sampling by injecting set-symmetric feedback at each diffusion step. SCG combines spectral set-point regulation, which aligns set-level statistics to real data via empirical characteristic function matching, with cooperative kernel coupling that stabilizes joint trajectories under noisy feedback. All computations operate on lightweight descriptors extracted from predicted clean latents, adding low overhead to the base method. We provide theoretical analysis including Lyapunov descent and input-to-state stability for distributional tracking. Experiments on ImageNette, ImageWoof, ImageNet-100 and ImageNet-1K show consistent accuracy gains across multiple diffusion-based baselines.</p>","absKo":"<p>Diffusion model은 dataset distillation의 generative prior로 활용되지만, 기존 파이프라인은 각 synthetic image를 독립적으로 진화시키는 per-sample update rule에 의존하여, 집합 전체 수준의 collective objective를 최적화하는 능력이 제한된다. 우리는 Set-Coupled Guidance(SCG)를 제안하는데, 이는 diffusion step마다 set-symmetric feedback을 주입하여 per-image sampling에서 group(IPC-at-once) sampling으로 전환하는 plug-and-play auxiliary controller이다. SCG는 spectral set-point regulation과 cooperative kernel coupling을 결합한다. 전자는 empirical characteristic function matching을 통해 set-level 통계를 real data에 정렬하고, 후자는 noisy feedback 하에서 joint trajectory를 안정화한다. 모든 계산은 predicted clean latent에서 추출한 lightweight descriptor 위에서 수행되므로, base method에 추가되는 오버헤드는 낮다. 우리는 Lyapunov descent와 distributional tracking에 대한 input-to-state stability를 포함한 이론적 분석을 제시한다. ImageNette, ImageWoof, ImageNet-100, ImageNet-1K 실험에서 여러 diffusion-based baseline 전반에 걸쳐 일관된 정확도 향상을 확인했다.</p>"},{"id":"62718","en":"LaTtE-Flow: Layerwise Timestep-Expert Flow-based Transformer","ko":"LaTtE-Flow: Layerwise Timestep-Expert Flow 기반 Transformer","authors":"Ying Shen, Zhiyang Xu, Jiuhai Chen, Shizhe Diao, Jiaxin Zhang, Yuguang Yao, Joy Rimchala, Ismini Lourentzou, Lifu Huang","pos":"#2612","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=dxVnCJRSm8","abs":"<p>Recent advances in multimodal foundation models unifying image understanding and generation have opened exciting avenues for tackling a wide range of vision-language tasks within a single framework. Despite progress, existing unified models typically require extensive pretraining, and many of these models suffer from slow image generation speeds, limiting their practical deployment in real-time or resource-constrained settings. In this work, we propose Layerwise Timestep-Expert Flow-based Transformer (LaTtE-Flow), a novel architecture that improves the efficiency of diffusion/flow-based transformer within the unified model setting. LaTtE-Flow builds upon powerful pretrained Vision-Language Models (VLMs) to inherit strong multimodal understanding capabilities, and extends them with a novel Layerwise Timestep Experts flow-based architecture for efficient image generation. LaTtE-Flow distributes the flow-matching process across specialized groups of Transformer layers, each responsible for a distinct subset of timesteps. This design significantly improves sampling efficiency by activating only a small subset of layers at each sampling timestep. To further enhance performance, we propose a Timestep-Conditioned Residual Attention mechanism for efficient information reuse across layers. Experiments demonstrate that LaTtE-Flow achieves strong performance on multimodal understanding tasks, while achieving competitive image generation quality with around 6× faster inference speed compared to recent unified multimodal models.</p>","absKo":"<p>이미지 이해와 생성을 통합하는 multimodal foundation model의 최근 발전은 단일 framework 내에서 광범위한 vision-language task를 다루기 위한 흥미로운 가능성을 열었다. 진전에도 불구하고, 기존 unified model은 대개 광범위한 pretraining을 요구하며, 이들 중 상당수는 느린 이미지 생성 속도로 인해 실시간 또는 자원 제약 환경에서의 실제 배치를 제한한다. 본 연구에서는 unified model 설정에서 diffusion/flow-based transformer의 효율을 향상시키는 새로운 architecture인 Layerwise Timestep-Expert Flow-based Transformer(LaTtE-Flow)를 제안한다. LaTtE-Flow는 강력한 pretrained Vision-Language Model(VLM)을 기반으로 하여 강한 multimodal understanding capability를 계승하고, 여기에 효율적인 이미지 생성을 위한 새로운 Layerwise Timestep Experts flow-based architecture를 확장한다. LaTtE-Flow는 flow-matching process를 특화된 Transformer layer 그룹들에 분산시키며, 각 그룹은 서로 다른 timestep의 하위 집합을 담당한다. 이러한 설계는 각 sampling timestep마다 일부 layer만 활성화함으로써 sampling efficiency를 크게 향상시킨다. 성능을 더욱 강화하기 위해, 우리는 layer 간 효율적인 정보 재사용을 위한 Timestep-Conditioned Residual Attention mechanism을 제안한다. 실험은 LaTtE-Flow가 multimodal understanding task에서 강력한 성능을 달성하는 동시에, 최근 unified multimodal model과 비교해 약 6배 빠른 inference speed로 경쟁력 있는 이미지 생성 품질을 제공함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"60727","en":"Towards Unified Multimodal Pretraining","ko":"통합 Multimodal Pretraining을 향하여","authors":"Shengbang Tong, David Fan, John Nguyen, Ellis Brown, Gaoyue Zhou, Shengyi Qian, Boyang Zheng, Théophane Vallaeys, Rob Fergus, Naila Murray, Marjan Ghazvininejad, Mike Lewis, Jakob Verbeek, Nicolas Ballas, Amir Bar, Michael Rabbat, Yann LeCun, Luke Zettlemoyer, Saining Xie, Koustuv Sinha","pos":"#2706","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=xAKrRYm6pc","abs":"<p>Unified multimodal models aim to input and output both vision and language data within a single system. In this work, we explore the design space of Unified Multimodal Pretraining through a controlled, from-scratch study. We find that leveraging a single high-dimensional semantic encoder (e.g. SigLIP 2) achieves the best combined performance for both visual understanding and generation. Furthermore, we observe that integrating diverse visual data---including raw video and image-text pairs---has minimal impact on language capabilities, suggesting that vision and text are compatible within a single unified model. We identify positive synergy where joint pretraining enhances downstream capabilities such as Visual Question Answering (VQA) and World Modeling. Turning to architecture, we investigate Mixture-of-Experts (MoE) design choices, such as granularity and sparsity, to identify an effective training recipe. Finally, we quantify scaling dynamics via IsoFLOP analysis and uncover a scaling asymmetry: language scaling is parameter-hungry, while vision scaling is significantly more data-hungry. We demonstrate that MoE architectures help address this imbalance by decoupling total parameter capacity from active compute, enabling the high capacity required for language while also accommodating the data-intensive nature of vision.</p>","absKo":"<p>Unified multimodal model은 하나의 시스템 안에서 vision과 language 데이터를 모두 입력하고 출력하는 것을 목표로 한다. 이 연구에서는 from-scratch controlled study를 통해 Unified Multimodal Pretraining의 설계 공간을 탐구한다. 우리는 단일한 고차원 semantic encoder(예: SigLIP 2)를 활용하는 것이 visual understanding과 generation 모두에서 가장 좋은 결합 성능을 달성함을 발견한다. 또한 raw video와 image-text pair를 포함한 다양한 visual data를 통합해도 language capability에는 거의 영향이 없음을 관찰했는데, 이는 vision과 text가 하나의 unified model 안에서 양립 가능함을 시사한다. 우리는 joint pretraining이 Visual Question Answering(VQA)과 World Modeling 같은 downstream capability를 향상시키는 positive synergy를 확인한다. architecture 측면에서는 효과적인 training recipe를 찾기 위해 granularity와 sparsity 같은 Mixture-of-Experts(MoE) 설계 선택을 조사한다. 마지막으로 IsoFLOP analysis를 통해 scaling dynamics를 정량화하고 scaling asymmetry를 밝혀낸다. language scaling은 parameter를 많이 필요로 하는 반면, vision scaling은 훨씬 더 많은 data를 필요로 한다. 우리는 MoE architecture가 total parameter capacity와 active compute를 분리함으로써 이 불균형을 해소하는 데 도움을 주며, language에 필요한 높은 capacity를 제공하는 동시에 vision의 데이터 집약적 특성도 수용할 수 있음을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"66317","en":"Iterative Refinement Neural Operators are Learned Fixed-Point Solvers: A Principled Approach to Spectral Bias Mitigation","ko":"반복 정제 Neural Operator는 학습된 고정점 해결기다: 스펙트럼 편향 완화를 위한 원칙적 접근법","authors":"Xiaotian Liu, Shuyuan Shang, Xiaopeng Wang, Pu Ren, Yaoqing Yang","pos":"#2800","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=4lAS8tI23u","abs":"<p>Neural operators serve as fast, data-driven surrogates for scientific modeling but typically rely on a monolithic, single-pass inference procedure that struggles to resolve high-frequency details, a limitation known as spectral bias. We introduce the Iterative Refinement Neural Operator (IRNO), which augments pre-trained operators with a learned refinement module iteratively applied via fixed-point iteration. IRNO decomposes the prediction into a coarse initialization followed by successive residual corrections, paralleling classical numerical solvers. Under mild assumptions, we establish contraction of the induced operator, ensuring convergence to a unique fixed point. To explicitly target high-frequency errors, we propose a progressive spectral loss that adaptively increases penalty on high-frequency components over refinement steps during training.  Across physical systems, IRNO consistently lowers error, with up to 56.05\\% improvement on turbulent flow. On Active Matter, spectral analysis reveals that, relative to base operator, the normalized error ratios decrease to 27.72–36.10\\% in low-, 5.07–6.68\\% in mid-, and 1.48–2.04\\% in high-frequencies, remaining stable beyond the trained iteration count.</p>"},{"id":"60923","en":"Preserving Plasticity in Continual Learning via Dynamical Isometry","ko":"Dynamical Isometry를 통한 Continual Learning의 Plasticity 보존","authors":"Andries Rosseau, Robert Müller, Ann Nowe","pos":"#2801","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=vJCOWSkMuq","abs":"<p>Continual training of deep neural networks under non-stationarity often leads to a progressive loss of plasticity, eventually limiting further learning. We define plasticity loss as the network’s diminishing ability to make reliable progress under gradient descent updates in all output-space directions, and identify departures from dynamical isometry (i.e., drift of the layer-wise Jacobian singular values away from one) as a key mechanism driving this loss. We first revisit a class of networks that are isometric almost-everywhere while remaining universal Lipschitz function approximators, demonstrating that isometry is compatible with expressive nonlinear function classes. Turning to more general architectures, we study an efficient isometry-promoting regularization scheme for continual learning. We analyze its interaction with common activation functions, and reveal a mechanism by which it can reactivate dead ReLU units. To integrate this regularization with adaptive optimization, we propose AdamO, an Adam-style optimizer that decouples isometric regularization from gradient updates, analogous to AdamW. Finally, we evaluate our methods in supervised and reinforcement learning settings designed to induce plasticity loss and show that they effectively preserve plasticity while also yielding strong performance.</p>","absKo":"<p>비정상성을 지닌 환경에서 deep neural network를 continual training하면 종종 plasticity가 점진적으로 상실되고, 결국 추가 학습이 제한된다. 우리는 plasticity loss를 gradient descent update에 의해 출력 공간의 모든 방향에서 네트워크가 신뢰할 수 있는 진전을 이루는 능력이 점차 감소하는 현상으로 정의하고, dynamical isometry에서의 이탈(즉, layer-wise Jacobian singular value가 1에서 벗어나는 drift)을 이러한 loss를 유발하는 핵심 메커니즘으로 식별한다. 먼저 우리는 거의 모든 곳에서 isometric이면서도 universal Lipschitz function approximator인 네트워크 계열을 재검토하여, isometry가 표현력 있는 비선형 함수 클래스와 양립 가능함을 보인다. 보다 일반적인 architecture로 시선을 돌려, 우리는 continual learning을 위한 효율적인 isometry-promoting regularization scheme을 연구한다. 우리는 그와 일반적인 activation function의 상호작용을 분석하고, dead ReLU unit을 재활성화할 수 있는 메커니즘을 밝힌다. 이 regularization을 adaptive optimization과 통합하기 위해, 우리는 AdamW와 유사하게 isometric regularization을 gradient update와 분리하는 Adam-style optimizer인 AdamO를 제안한다. 마지막으로, 우리는 plasticity loss를 유도하도록 설계된 supervised 및 reinforcement learning 설정에서 우리의 방법을 평가하고, 이들이 plasticity를 효과적으로 보존하면서도 강한 성능을 낸다는 것을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"62645","en":"Prototype-Based Test-Time Adaptation of Vision-Language Models","ko":"Vision-Language Models의 Prototype-Based Test-Time Adaptation","authors":"Zhaohong Huang, Yuxin Zhang, Wenjing Liu, Fei Chao, Rongrong Ji","pos":"#2802","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ejmfnVdW2X","abs":"<p>Test-time adaptation (TTA) has emerged as a promising paradigm for vision–language models (VLMs) to bridge the distribution gap between pre-training and test data. Recent works have focused on backpropagation-free TTA methods that rely on cache-based designs, but these introduce two key limitations. First, inference latency increases as the cache grows with the number of classes, leading to inefficiencies in large-scale settings. Second, suboptimal performance occurs when the cache contains insufficient or incorrect samples. In this paper, we present Prototype-Based Test-Time Adaptation (PTA), an efficient and effective TTA paradigm that uses a set of class-specific knowledge prototypes to accumulate knowledge from test samples. Particularly, knowledge prototypes are adaptively weighted based on the zero-shot class confidence of each test sample, incorporating the sample's visual features into the corresponding class-specific prototype. It is worth highlighting that the knowledge from past test samples is integrated and utilized solely in the prototypes, eliminating the overhead of cache population and retrieval that hinders the efficiency of existing TTA methods. This endows PTA with extremely high efficiency while achieving state-of-the-art performance on 15 image recognition benchmarks and 4 robust point cloud analysis benchmarks. For example, PTA improves CLIP’s accuracy from 65.64\\% to 69.38\\% on 10 cross-domain benchmarks, while retaining 92\\% of CLIP’s inference speed on large-scale ImageNet-1K. In contrast, the cache-based TDA achieves a lower accuracy of 67.97\\% and operates at only 50\\% of CLIP’s inference speed.</p>","absKo":"<p>Test-time adaptation (TTA)은 pre-training과 test data 사이의 distribution gap을 메우기 위해 vision–language models (VLMs)에 유망한 패러다임으로 부상했다. 최근 연구들은 cache 기반 설계에 의존하는 backpropagation-free TTA 방법에 집중해 왔지만, 이는 두 가지 핵심 한계를 낳는다. 첫째, cache가 class 수에 따라 커지면서 inference latency가 증가해 대규모 환경에서 비효율적이다. 둘째, cache에 충분하지 않거나 잘못된 sample이 포함되면 성능이 저하된다. 본 논문에서는 test sample로부터 knowledge를 축적하기 위해 class-specific knowledge prototype 집합을 사용하는 효율적이고 효과적인 TTA 패러다임인 Prototype-Based Test-Time Adaptation (PTA)를 제안한다. 특히 knowledge prototype은 각 test sample의 zero-shot class confidence를 바탕으로 적응적으로 가중되며, sample의 visual feature를 대응하는 class-specific prototype에 통합한다. 주목할 점은 과거 test sample의 knowledge가 오직 prototype 안에서만 통합되고 활용된다는 점으로, 기존 TTA 방법의 효율성을 저해하는 cache population과 retrieval의 오버헤드를 제거한다. 이를 통해 PTA는 매우 높은 효율성을 가지면서도 15개의 image recognition benchmark와 4개의 robust point cloud analysis benchmark에서 state-of-the-art performance를 달성한다. 예를 들어, PTA는 10개의 cross-domain benchmark에서 CLIP의 accuracy를 65.64%에서 69.38%로 향상시키고, 대규모 ImageNet-1K에서 CLIP inference speed의 92%를 유지한다. 반면 cache 기반 TDA는 더 낮은 67.97%의 accuracy를 보이며 CLIP inference speed의 50%에서만 동작한다.</p>"},{"id":"62138","en":"Rethinking Calibration for Early-Exit Neural Networks","ko":"Early-Exit Neural Network를 위한 Calibration 재고","authors":"Piotr Kubaty, Filip Szatkowski, Grzegorz Choczyński, Bartosz Wójcik, Eric Nalisnick","pos":"#2803","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=jTtfB7ur5m","abs":"<p>Early-exit neural networks~(EENNs) accelerate inference by allowing intermediate classifiers to stop computation once predictions are confident enough. Most methods rely on confidence thresholds for exiting, and consequently, classifier calibration is widely assumed to improve performance. In this work, we challenge this assumption and show that calibration is often not suitable for EENNs through a detailed theoretical study. To address the limitations of calibration, we introduce Early-Exit Failure Prediction~(EEFP), which accounts for both prediction correctness and the cost of further computation. We also propose a lightweight, EEFP-motivated procedure to improve the intermediate classifiers, which can directly replace calibration in EENNs. Extensive experiments demonstrate that our approach achieves superior cost–accuracy trade-offs than calibration and discuss how EEFP measures more reliably reflect overall EENN performance.</p>","absKo":"<p>Early-exit neural network(EENN)는 중간 classifier가 예측이 충분히 확신적일 때 계산을 중단하도록 함으로써 inference를 가속한다. 대부분의 방법은 exit를 위해 confidence threshold에 의존하며, 그 결과 classifier calibration이 성능 향상에 도움이 된다고 널리 가정된다. 본 연구에서는 이 가정에 도전하며, 세부적인 이론 연구를 통해 calibration이 EENN에 종종 적합하지 않음을 보인다. Calibration의 한계를 해결하기 위해 우리는 Early-Exit Failure Prediction(EEFP)을 도입하는데, 이는 예측의 정답 여부와 추가 계산 비용을 모두 고려한다. 또한 EENN에서 calibration을 직접 대체할 수 있는, EEFP에 기반한 경량의 intermediate classifier 개선 절차도 제안한다. 광범위한 실험은 우리의 접근이 calibration보다 더 우수한 cost-accuracy trade-off를 달성함을 보여주며, EEFP measure가 전체 EENN 성능을 더 신뢰성 있게 반영하는 방식에 대해서도 논의한다.</p>"},{"id":"64388","en":"Spectral Collapse Drives Loss of Plasticity in Deep Continual Learning","ko":"스펙트럼 붕괴가 심층 지속 학습에서 가소성 상실을 유발한다","authors":"Arjun Prakash, Naicheng He, Kaicheng Guo, Saket Tiwari, Tyrone Serapio, Ruo Yu Tao, Amy Greenwald, George Konidaris","pos":"#2804","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=O6rHSkpYJU","abs":"We investigate why deep neural networks suffer from loss of plasticity in deep continual learning, failing to learn new tasks without reinitializing parameters. We show that this failure is preceded by Hessian spectral collapse at new-task initialization, where meaningful curvature directions vanish and gradient descent becomes ineffective. Analyzing a linearized ReLU network, we derive explicit $\\epsilon $-rank conditions for successful training and prove that the loss-weighted Gram matrix is spectrally equivalent to the Generalized Gauss-Newton approximation, bridging NTK dynamics to Hessian curvature. Targeting spectral collapse directly, we then discuss the Kronecker factored approximation of the Hessian, which motivates two regularization enhancements: maintaining high effective feature rank and applying L2 penalties. Experiments on continual supervised and reinforcement learning tasks confirm that combining these two regularizers effectively preserves plasticity.","absKo":"우리는 deep continual learning에서 deep neural network가 왜 loss of plasticity를 겪어, 파라미터를 재초기화하지 않으면 새로운 task를 학습하지 못하는지 조사한다. 우리는 이 실패가 새로운 task 초기화 시점의 Hessian spectral collapse에 앞서 발생함을 보이며, 이때 의미 있는 curvature 방향이 사라지고 gradient descent가 비효율적으로 된다. Linearized ReLU network를 분석하여, 성공적인 학습을 위한 명시적 $\\epsilon$-rank condition을 유도하고, loss-weighted Gram matrix가 Generalized Gauss-Newton approximation과 spectrally equivalent하다는 것을 증명하여 NTK dynamics와 Hessian curvature를 연결한다. spectral collapse를 직접 겨냥하여, 이후 우리는 Hessian의 Kronecker factored approximation을 논의하고, 이를 바탕으로 두 가지 regularization enhancement를 제안한다. 높은 effective feature rank를 유지하는 것과 L2 penalty를 적용하는 것이다. continual supervised learning과 reinforcement learning task에서의 실험은 이 두 regularizer를 결합하면 plasticity를 효과적으로 보존함을 확인한다."},{"id":"66344","en":"Connecting Independently Trained Modes via Layer-Wise Connectivity","ko":"계층별 연결성을 통한 독립 훈련된 모드 연결","authors":"Yongding Tian, Zaid Al-Ars, Maksim Kitsak, H Peter Hofstee","pos":"#2902","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=4VOTzpH9MO","abs":"<p>Empirical studies have shown that continuous low-loss paths can be constructed between independently trained neural network models.  This phenomenon, known as mode connectivity, refers to the existence of such paths between distinct modes-i.e., well-trained solutions in parameter space.  However, existing empirical methods do not reliably connect independently trained modes and have been evaluated mainly on a narrow set of architectures (e.g., basic CNNs, VGG, and ResNet), leaving their effectiveness on newer models unclear. In this work, we propose a new empirical algorithm for connecting independently trained modes that generalizes beyond traditional architectures and supports a broader range of networks, including MobileNet, ShuffleNet, EfficientNet, RegNet, Deep Layer Aggregation (DLA), and Compact Convolutional Transformers (CCT).  In addition to broader applicability, the proposed method yields more consistent connectivity paths across independently trained mode pairs and supports connecting modes obtained with different training hyperparameters.</p>"},{"id":"65316","en":"Who Said Neural Networks Aren't Linear?","ko":"누가 신경망이 선형이 아니라고 했는가?","authors":"Nimrod Berman, Assaf Hallak, Assaf Shocher","pos":"#2903","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Eqm5VEaAom","abs":"Neural networks are famously nonlinear. However, linearity is defined relative to a pair of vector spaces, $f:\\mathcal{X}\\to\\mathcal{Y}$. Leveraging the algebraic concept of transport of structure, we propose a method to explicitly identify non-standard vector spaces where a neural network acts as a linear operator. When sandwiching a linear operator $A$ between two invertible neural networks, $f(x)=g_y^{-1}(A g_x(x))$, the corresponding vector spaces $\\mathcal{X}$ and $\\mathcal{Y}$ are induced by newly defined addition and scaling actions derived from $g_x$ and $g_y$. We term this kind of architecture a Linearizer. This framework makes the entire arsenal of linear algebra, including SVD, pseudo-inverse, orthogonal projection and more, applicable to nonlinear mappings. Furthermore, we show that the composition of two Linearizers that share a neural network is also a Linearizer. We leverage this property and demonstrate that training diffusion models using our architecture makes the hundreds of sampling steps collapse into a single step. We further utilize our framework to enforce idempotency (i.e.\\ $f(f(x))=f(x)$) on networks leading to a globally projective generative model and to demonstrate modular style transfer."},{"id":"62593","en":"Symmetry Reveals the In-Context Classifier: Transformers Implement Mean-Shift Dynamics","ko":"대칭성이 In-Context Classifier를 드러냄: Transformers의 Mean-Shift Dynamics 구현","authors":"Patrick Lutz, Themistoklis Haris, Arjun Chandra, Aditya Gangrade, Venkatesh Saligrama","pos":"#2906","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=fDMizWsNoG","abs":"<p>Transformers can perform in-context classification from a few labeled examples, yet the inference-time algorithm remains opaque. We study multi-class linear classification in the hard no-margin regime and make the computation identifiable by enforcing feature- and label-permutation equivariance at every layer. This enables interpretability while maintaining functional equivalence and yields highly structured weights. From these models we extract an explicit depth-indexed recursion---an end-to-end identified, emergent update rule inside a standard softmax transformer, to our knowledge the first of its kind. Attention matrices formed from mixed feature--label Gram structure drive coupled updates of training points, labels, and the test probe. The resulting dynamics implement label-aware mean-shift, which provably amplifies class separation and yields robust expected class alignment.</p>","absKo":"<p>Transformer는 소수의 labeled example만으로 in-context classification을 수행할 수 있지만, inference-time 알고리즘은 여전히 불투명하다. 우리는 hard no-margin regime에서의 multi-class linear classification을 연구하고, 각 layer에서 feature- 및 label-permutation equivariance를 강제함으로써 계산을 identifiable하게 만든다. 이를 통해 기능적 동등성을 유지하면서도 해석 가능성을 확보하고, 매우 구조화된 weight를 얻는다. 이 모델들로부터 우리는 명시적인 depth-indexed recursion을 추출한다. 이는 표준 softmax transformer 내부에 존재하는 end-to-end identified, emergent update rule로서, 우리가 아는 한 최초의 사례이다. 혼합된 feature--label Gram structure에서 형성된 attention matrix는 training point, label, test probe의 결합된 업데이트를 구동한다. 그 결과 나타나는 dynamics는 label-aware mean-shift를 구현하며, 이는 class separation을 이론적으로 증폭시키고 견고한 expected class alignment을 유도한다.</p>"},{"id":"61442","en":"Depth-Progressive Monotonic Learning without Backpropagation","ko":"Backpropagation 없는 깊이 점진적 단조 학습","authors":"Chenhao Ye, Rongguang Ye, Yuchao Zhang, Ming Tang","pos":"#3001","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=q3nEaVeIYZ","abs":"<p>Backpropagation (BP) remains the dominant training paradigm for deep neural networks, yet its reliance on global gradient propagation fundamentally induces update locking problem, enforcing strong inter-layer dependencies in parameter updates. To address this limitation, we propose Depth-progressive Monotonic Learning (DMoL), a training scheme that assigns layer-wise local belief objectives and incrementally refines them across network depth, enabling unlocked parameter updates. As a result, DMoL supports dynamic modification of network depth during training, adapting to available compute and device resources while maintaining stable optimization. We provide theoretical guarantees that layer-wise local belief objectives improve monotonically with increasing depth and converge exponentially. Empirically, DMoL consistently matches or outperforms BP across diverse tasks, yielding a 4.3\\% accuracy gain on CIFAR-100, mitigating over-smoothing in deep graph neural networks (+37.5\\% on Cora), and reducing the final loss by over 35\\% in diffusion model training, highlighting its robustness and flexibility as an alternative to BP. The code is publicly available at: https://anonymous.4open.science/r/DMoL.</p>","absKo":"<p>Backpropagation(BP)은 여전히 deep neural network 학습의 지배적인 패러다임이지만, global gradient propagation에 의존하기 때문에 본질적으로 update locking problem을 유발하며 parameter update에서 강한 inter-layer dependency를 강제한다. 이 한계를 해결하기 위해 우리는 layer-wise local belief objective를 할당하고 network depth 전반에 걸쳐 이를 점진적으로 refine하는 training scheme인 Depth-progressive Monotonic Learning(DMoL)을 제안하며, 이를 통해 unlocked parameter update를 가능하게 한다. 그 결과 DMoL은 학습 중 network depth를 동적으로 수정할 수 있어, 안정적인 optimization을 유지하면서 available compute와 device resource에 적응한다. 우리는 layer-wise local belief objective가 depth가 증가함에 따라 단조롭게 개선되고 지수적으로 수렴함을 이론적으로 보장한다. 실험적으로 DMoL은 다양한 task에서 BP와 일관되게 비슷하거나 더 나은 성능을 보이며, CIFAR-100에서 4.3\\% accuracy 향상, deep graph neural network에서 over-smoothing 완화(+37.5\\% on Cora), diffusion model training에서 최종 loss를 35\\% 이상 감소시키는 성과를 보여 BP의 대안으로서 강인성과 유연성을 입증한다. 코드는 공개되어 있다: https://anonymous.4open.science/r/DMoL.</p>"},{"id":"66642","en":"Kuramoto Oscillatory Phase Encoding: Neuro-inspired Synchronization for Improved Learning Efficiency","ko":"Kuramoto 진동 위상 부호화: 학습 효율 향상을 위한 신경 영감 동기화","authors":"Mingqing Xiao, Yansen Wang, Dongqi Han, Caihua Shan, Dongsheng Li","pos":"#3002","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=1rSqVUl7l3","abs":"<p>Spatiotemporal neural dynamics and oscillatory synchronization are widely implicated in biological information processing and have been hypothesized to support flexible coordination such as feature binding. By contrast, most deep learning architectures represent and propagate information through activation values, neglecting the joint dynamics of rate and phase. In this work, we introduce Kuramoto oscillatory Phase Encoding (KoPE) as an additional, evolving phase state to Vision Transformers, incorporating a neuro-inspired synchronization mechanism to advance learning efficiency. We show that KoPE can improve training, parameter, and data efficiency of vision models through synchronization-enhanced structure learning. Moreover, KoPE benefits tasks requiring structured understanding, including semantic and panoptic segmentation, representation alignment with language, and few-shot abstract visual reasoning (ARC-AGI). Theoretical analysis and empirical verification further suggest that KoPE can accelerate attention concentration for learning efficiency. These results indicate that synchronization can serve as a scalable, neuro-inspired mechanism for advancing state-of-the-art neural network models.</p>"},{"id":"64627","en":"Seeing is Solving: Unlocking Efficient Multimodal RL via View Alignment","ko":"보는 것이 곧 푸는 것: View Alignment를 통한 효율적 멀티모달 RL 실현","authors":"Qinsi Wang, Jing Shi, Kun Wan, Handong Zhao, Hancheng Ye, Zishan Shao, Jinghan Ke, Yudong Liu, Daniel Miranda, Purvak Lapsiya, Yiran Chen, Wentian Zhao","pos":"#4014","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=LYBcBH3Y76","abs":"<p>Although Reinforcement Learning Fine-Tuning (RLFT) applied to Vision-Language Models (VLMs) substantially enhances multimodal reasoning capabilities, their prohibitive training cost limits broad adoption. Surprisingly, most existing methods simply port Large Language Model (LLM) RLFT techniques to VLMs, while ignoring a intrinsic property of multimodal models: their dynamic text–vision alignment. We ask a new question: Can this intrinsic alignment be turned into a training signal that makes VLM RLFT more efficient? We analyze how a VLM plans to attend, actually attends, and ideally should attend during reasoning, and derive two lightweight metrics from these patterns. Predictive View Accuracy (PVA) estimates sample difficulty, and Reasoning View Accuracy (RVA) reflects the quality of chain-of-thought (CoT) reasoning. These alignment signals enable automated data curriculum and dense reasoning supervision. We introduce FOCUS-RL, a plug-and-play framework that can be seamlessly integrated into any VLM and dramatically boosts RLFT training efficiency. FOCUS-RL achieves 2.5 x – 4 x faster convergence over vanilla GRPO and consistent accuracy gains (+4.4 on average) across six different benchmarks and multiple VLM families.</p>","absKo":"<p>Vision-Language Models (VLMs)에 적용된 Reinforcement Learning Fine-Tuning (RLFT)은 multimodal reasoning capability를 크게 향상시키지만, 과도한 training cost 때문에 널리 채택되기 어렵다. 놀랍게도 기존 방법의 대부분은 Large Language Model (LLM) RLFT 기법을 VLM에 단순 이식하면서, multimodal model의 내재적 특성인 dynamic text–vision alignment를 간과한다. 우리는 새로운 질문을 던진다: 이 내재적 alignment를 VLM RLFT를 더 효율적으로 만드는 training signal로 활용할 수 있는가? 우리는 VLM이 reasoning 중에 어떻게 attend할 계획을 세우는지, 실제로 어떻게 attention을 수행하는지, 그리고 이상적으로는 어떻게 attend해야 하는지를 분석하고, 이러한 패턴으로부터 두 개의 경량 metric을 도출한다. Predictive View Accuracy (PVA)는 sample difficulty를 추정하고, Reasoning View Accuracy (RVA)는 chain-of-thought (CoT) reasoning의 품질을 반영한다. 이 alignment signal은 자동 data curriculum과 dense reasoning supervision을 가능하게 한다. 우리는 어떤 VLM에도 매끄럽게 통합될 수 있고 RLFT training efficiency를 극적으로 향상시키는 plug-and-play framework인 FOCUS-RL을 소개한다. FOCUS-RL은 vanilla GRPO 대비 2.5 x – 4 x 빠른 수렴을 달성하며, 여섯 개의 서로 다른 benchmark와 여러 VLM family 전반에서 일관된 정확도 향상(+4.4 평균)을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"64295","en":"Little By Little: Continual Learning via Incremental Mixture of Rank-1 Associative Memory Experts","ko":"조금씩: 계수-1 연상 메모리 전문가의 증분 혼합을 통한 지속 학습","authors":"Haodong Lu, Chongyang Zhao, Minhui Xue, Lina Yao, Kristen Moore, Dong Gong","pos":"#4200","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=P247k4ELcn","abs":"<p>Continual learning (CL) with large pre-trained models is challenged by task interference and catastrophic forgetting. Existing LoRA-based Mixture-of-Experts (MoE) methods mitigate forgetting by adding new task-specific adapters and freezing old ones, but often suffer from redundancy, interference, and ambiguous routing due to coarse-grained experts and routing. Coarse-grained experts (i.e., full LoRA adapters with large rank) encode low-specialty information. Newly added experts often duplicate or conflict with existing ones, causing redundancy and interference. Their low specialization further confuses the router, accelerating routing degradation and forgetting as experts accumulate. In this work, we propose MoRAM (Mixture of Rank-1 Associative Memory). Grounded in the view that weight matrices function as linear associative memories, MoRAM achieves CL as gradual incrementing of atomic rank-1 memory experts. Each rank-1 adapter acts as a fine-grained MoE expert or an associative memory unit. By viewing rank-1 adapters as key–value pairs, we eliminate explicit routers in MoE-LoRA, using a self-activation mechanism where each memory atom evaluates its own relevance via its intrinsic key. This transforms the adaptation process into robust, content-addressable retrieval. Extensive experiments on CLIP and LLMs demonstrate that \\ours significantly outperforms state-of-the-art baselines, achieving superior plasticity-stability trade-offs, improving generalization while mitigating forgetting.</p>","absKo":"<p>대형 사전학습 모델을 사용하는 continual learning (CL)은 task interference와 catastrophic forgetting이라는 도전에 직면합니다. 기존의 LoRA 기반 Mixture-of-Experts (MoE) 방법은 새로운 task-specific adapter를 추가하고 기존 것은 고정함으로써 forgetting을 완화하지만, coarse-grained expert와 routing 때문에 redundancy, interference, ambiguous routing 문제가 자주 발생합니다. coarse-grained expert, 즉 큰 rank를 가진 전체 LoRA adapter는 낮은 특화도의 정보를 인코딩합니다. 새로 추가된 expert는 기존 것과 중복되거나 충돌하는 경우가 많아 redundancy와 interference를 유발합니다. 또한 낮은 특화도는 router를 더 혼란스럽게 만들어 expert가 누적될수록 routing degradation과 forgetting을 가속합니다. 본 연구에서는 MoRAM (Mixture of Rank-1 Associative Memory)을 제안합니다. 가중치 행렬이 선형 associative memory로 기능한다는 관점에 기반하여, MoRAM은 atomic rank-1 memory expert를 점진적으로 늘려가는 방식으로 CL을 달성합니다. 각 rank-1 adapter는 fine-grained MoE expert 또는 associative memory unit으로 작동합니다. rank-1 adapter를 key-value pair로 보는 관점을 통해, MoE-LoRA에서 explicit router를 제거하고 각 memory atom이 자신의 intrinsic key를 통해 관련성을 평가하는 self-activation mechanism을 사용합니다. 이는 adaptation 과정을 강건한 content-addressable retrieval로 변환합니다. CLIP과 LLM에 대한 광범위한 실험은 \\ours가 state-of-the-art baseline을 크게 능가하며, 더 우수한 plasticity-stability trade-off를 달성하고, forgetting을 완화하면서 generalization을 향상시킴을 보여줍니다.</p>"},{"id":"66418","en":"The Generalization Spectrum: A Chromatographic Approach to Evaluating Learning Algorithms","ko":"일반화 스펙트럼: 학습 알고리즘 평가를 위한 크로마토그래피 접근법","authors":"Jinghan Zhang, Zerui Cheng, Shiqi Chen, Ge Zhang, Wenhao Huang, Jiashuo Liu, Junxian He, Tianle Cai","pos":"#4300","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=3urFJKbmYN","abs":"<p>Traditional evaluations measure a learning algorithm's final performance on an i.i.d. test set, reducing learning to a single aggregate score. This approach obscures a fundamental question: to what extent does learning from a specific example generalize to others? Such per-sample generalization—akin to learning by analogy in human cognition—captures how far the knowledge extracted from one example can transfer, yet remains invisible to standard benchmarks.  We introduce the Generalization Spectrum, an evaluation framework designed to expose this hidden dimension. For each training example, we construct a controlled suite of test variants arranged by increasing transfer distance—from exact recall to implementation transfer across languages, context transfer under complete narrative re-framing, category-matched in-domain problems, and an unpaired baseline. By tracking performance across these distances, we reveal not just whether an algorithm learns, but how far that learning extends. We instantiate this framework on competitive programming, using a synthetic generation pipeline seeded with recent problems to mitigate contamination.   Across ICL, SFT, RFT, and RL, we find two levers that shape generalization radius: \\textbf{(i) the learning algorithm}---how to learn from a fixed set of training instances---where RL yields markedly stronger near-transfer than SFT/RFT under matched memorization and learns more transferable structure; and \\textbf{(ii) the learning content}---what extra signal to provide or reformat given the same seeds---where abstract ICL demonstrations and on-policy SFT targets yield more reliable transfer than concrete code and off-policy supervision.</p>"},{"id":"66628","en":"CAffNet: Hard Constraint-Affine Neural Networks","ko":"CAffNet: Hard Constraint-Affine 신경망","authors":"Yang Zhao, Jungeun Lee, Jeong hwan Jeon, Sze Zheng Yong","pos":"#4303","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=20hdQQQrA4","abs":"<p>We present a novel framework for embedding hard constraint satisfaction into neural network (NN) architectures, specifically feedforward neural networks and transformers, with input-dependent affine constraints of arbitrary cardinality. Traditional constraint enforcement approaches either rely on penalty-based soft constraints, which offer no guarantee of satisfaction, or on post-processing methods that enforce constraints after the NN is trained, which may lead to suboptimality. We introduce a trainable constraint-affine (CAffine) layer into NNs, yielding CAffNet, which goes beyond enforcing affine constraints via fixed orthogonal or parallel projections and enables joint optimization with network parameters. Moreover, we impose no restrictions on the constraint space dimensions and establish that our construction preserves the universal approximation properties of NNs, while providing provable guarantees on constraint adherence for all inputs. Experimental validation demonstrates robust performance across diverse domains requiring guaranteed constraint satisfaction.</p>"},{"id":"62583","en":"Data Agent: Learning to Select Data via End-to-End Dynamic Optimization","ko":"Data Agent: 엔드투엔드 동적 최적화를 통한 데이터 선택 학습","authors":"Suorong Yang, Fangjian Su, Hai Gan, Ziqi Ye, Jie Li, Baile Xu, Furao Shen, Soujanya Poria","pos":"#4312","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=fKe6zvEZEE","abs":"<p>Dynamic Data selection aims to accelerate training by prioritizing informative samples during online training. However, existing methods typically rely on task-specific handcrafted metrics or static/snapshot-based criteria to estimate sample importance, limiting scalability across learning paradigms and making it difficult to capture the evolving utility of data throughout training. To address this challenge, we propose Data Agent, an end-to-end dynamic data selection framework that formulates data selection as a training-aware sequential decision-making problem. The agent learns a sample-wise selection policy that co-evolves with model optimization, guided by a composite reward that integrates loss-based difficulty and confidence-based uncertainty signals. The reward signals capture complementary objectives of optimization impact and information gain, together with a tuning-free adaptive weighting mechanism that balances these signals over training. Extensive experiments across a wide range of datasets and architectures demonstrate that Data Agent consistently accelerates training while preserving or improving performance, e.g., reducing costs by over 50\\% on ImageNet-1k and MMLU with lossless performance. Moreover, its dataset-agnostic formulation and modular reward make it plug-and-play across tasks and scenarios, e.g., robustness to noisy datasets, highlighting its potential in real-world scenarios.</p>","absKo":"<p>Dynamic Data selection은 online training 동안 유익한 sample을 우선순위화하여 training을 가속하는 것을 목표로 한다. 그러나 기존 방법은 보통 task-specific한 handcrafted metric이나 static/snapshot 기반 criterion에 의존해 sample importance를 추정하므로, 학습 패러다임 전반으로의 확장성이 제한되고 training 전반에 걸쳐 데이터의 변화하는 효용을 포착하기 어렵다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 data selection을 training-aware sequential decision-making problem으로 정식화하는 end-to-end dynamic data selection framework인 Data Agent를 제안한다. 이 agent는 loss 기반 difficulty와 confidence 기반 uncertainty signal을 통합하는 composite reward의 지도를 받아 model optimization과 co-evolve하는 sample-wise selection policy를 학습한다. reward signal은 optimization impact와 information gain이라는 상보적 objective를 포착하며, 튜닝이 필요 없는 adaptive weighting mechanism이 training 동안 이 signal의 균형을 맞춘다. 다양한 dataset과 architecture에 걸친 광범위한 실험은 Data Agent가 성능을 유지하거나 향상시키면서 training을 일관되게 가속함을 보여준다. 예를 들어 ImageNet-1k와 MMLU에서 lossless performance로 비용을 50% 이상 줄인다. 또한 dataset-agnostic formulation과 modular reward는 noisy dataset에 대한 robustness 등 다양한 task와 scenario에서 plug-and-play로 동작하게 하며, 실제 환경에서의 잠재력을 강조한다.</p>"},{"id":"61666","en":"Dual-stage Contrastive Learning-enhanced Multi-view Variational Clustering","ko":"Dual-stage Contrastive Learning으로 강화한 Multi-view Variational Clustering","authors":"Yanxi Liu, Fangxi Liu, Yipin Hu, Yanwei Yu, Lei Meng, Yongyong Chen, Guoqing Chao","pos":"#4313","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=nx6mKQByB5","abs":"<p>Multi-view clustering aims to obtain a consensus clustering by integrating complementary and consistent information from multiple views. However, two critical challenges still exist in variational methods: (1) view heterogeneity and noise often make fusion unreliable; (2)  ambiguous posteriors and misassigned boundary samples impact the clustering performance. To address these issues, we propose Dual-stage Contrastive Learning-enhanced Multi-view Variational Clustering (DCL-MVC), which integrates contrastive learning into both the fusion and representation stages. Firstly, at the fusion stage, we introduce a fusion-then-attention mechanism to capture cross-view interactions and learn view-level attention weights for building a unified and reliable fused representation, and further introduce instance-level contrastive learning to enforce cross-view alignment at the instance level. Secondly, we focus on boundary samples with uncertain posteriors and refine their cluster assignments by using cluster-center contrastive loss to enlarge inter-cluster margins, while leveraging prototypical contrastive learning with a confidence-aware curriculum to promote intra-cluster compactness at the representation stage. Extensive experiments on six real-world datasets demonstrate consistent improvements over strong baselines and validate the contribution of each component.</p>","absKo":"<p>Multi-view clustering은 여러 view에서 보완적이고 일관된 정보를 통합하여 합의(consensus) clustering을 얻는 것을 목표로 합니다. 그러나 variational method에는 여전히 두 가지 중요한 문제가 존재합니다. (1) view heterogeneity와 noise로 인해 fusion이 불안정해지기 쉽습니다. (2) 모호한 posterior와 잘못 할당된 boundary sample이 clustering 성능에 영향을 미칩니다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 fusion stage와 representation stage 모두에 contrastive learning을 통합한 Dual-stage Contrastive Learning-enhanced Multi-view Variational Clustering (DCL-MVC)을 제안합니다. 첫째, fusion stage에서는 fusion-then-attention mechanism을 도입하여 cross-view interaction을 포착하고 view-level attention weight를 학습함으로써 통합되고 신뢰할 수 있는 fused representation을 구축하며, 추가로 instance-level contrastive learning을 도입하여 instance 수준에서 cross-view alignment를 강제합니다. 둘째, 우리는 posterior가 불확실한 boundary sample에 집중하고, cluster-center contrastive loss를 사용해 inter-cluster margin을 넓히는 동시에, confidence-aware curriculum을 갖춘 prototypical contrastive learning을 활용하여 representation stage에서 intra-cluster compactness를 촉진함으로써 이들의 cluster assignment를 정교화합니다. 여섯 개의 실제 데이터셋에 대한 광범위한 실험은 강력한 baseline 대비 일관된 향상을 보여주며 각 구성 요소의 기여를 검증합니다.</p>"},{"id":"66720","en":"SpecPL: Disentangling Spectral Granularity for Prompt Learning","ko":"SpecPL: Prompt Learning을 위한 Spectral Granularity 분리","authors":"Jingtao Zhou, Xirui Kang, feiyang huang, Lai Man Po","pos":"#806","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=118JD1BQxO","abs":"<p>Existing prompt learning for VLMs exhibits a modality asymmetry, predominantly optimizing text tokens while still relying on frozen visual encoder as holistic extractor and neglecting the spectral granularity essential for fine-grained discrimination. To bridge this, we introduce Disentangling Spectral Granularity for Prompt Learning (SpecPL), which approaches prompt learning from a novel spectral perspective via Counterfactual Granule Supervision. Specifically, we leverage a frozen VAE to decompose visual signals into semantic low-frequency bands and granular high-frequency details. A frozen Visual Semantic Bank anchors text representations to universal low-frequency invariants, mitigating overfitting. Crucially, fine-grained discrimination is driven by counterfactual granule training: by permuting high-frequency signals, we compel the model to explicitly distinguish visual granularity from semantic invariance. Uniquely, SpecPL serves as a universal plug-and-play booster, revitalizing text-oriented baselines like CoOp and MaPLe via visual-side guidance. Experiments on 11 benchmarks demonstrate competitive state-of-the-art performance, achieving a new performance ceiling of 81.51\\% harmonic-mean accuracy. These results validate that spectral disentanglement with counterfactual supervision effectively bridges the gap in the stability-generalization trade-off.</p>"},{"id":"62575","en":"Residual Context Diffusion Language Models","ko":"잔차 문맥 Diffusion 언어 모델","authors":"Yuezhou Hu, Harman Singh, Monishwaran Maheswaran, Haocheng Xi, Coleman Hooper, Jintao Zhang, Aditya Tomar, Michael Mahoney, Sewon Min, Mehrdad Farajtabar, Kurt Keutzer, Amir Gholaminejad, Chenfeng Xu","pos":"#4604","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=fQYwAlpK3V","abs":"Diffusion Large Language Models (dLLMs) have emerged as a promising alternative to purely autoregressive language models because they can decode multiple tokens in parallel. However, state-of-the-art block-wise dLLMs rely on a ``remasking\" mechanism that decodes only the most confident tokens and discards the rest, effectively wasting computation. We demonstrate that recycling computation from the discarded tokens is beneficial, as these tokens retain contextual information useful for subsequent decoding iterations. In light of this, we propose Residual Context Diffusion (RCD), a module that converts these discarded token representations into contextual residuals and injects them back for the next denoising step. RCD uses a decoupled two-stage training pipeline to bypass the memory bottlenecks associated with backpropagation. We validate our method on both long CoT reasoning (SDAR) and short CoT instruction following (LLaDA) models. We demonstrate that a standard dLLM can be efficiently converted to the RCD paradigm with merely $\\sim$1 billion tokens. RCD consistently improves frontier dLLMs by 5--10 points in accuracy with minimal extra computation overhead across a wide range of benchmarks. Notably, on the most challenging AIME tasks, RCD nearly doubles baseline accuracy and attains up to 4--5x fewer denoising steps at equivalent accuracy levels.","absKo":"Diffusion Large Language Model (dLLM)은 여러 token을 병렬로 decode할 수 있기 때문에 순수 autoregressive language model의 유망한 대안으로 떠올랐다. 그러나 최신 block-wise dLLM은 가장 자신 있는 token만 decode하고 나머지는 버리는 ``remasking'' 메커니즘에 의존하므로, 사실상 계산을 낭비한다. 우리는 버려진 token이 이후 decoding iteration에 유용한 contextual information을 보존하고 있음을 보이며, 이 계산을 재활용하는 것이 이롭다는 점을 입증한다. 이를 바탕으로 우리는 버려진 token representation을 contextual residual로 변환해 다음 denoising step에 다시 주입하는 module인 Residual Context Diffusion (RCD)을 제안한다. RCD는 backpropagation과 관련된 memory bottleneck을 우회하기 위해 decoupled two-stage training pipeline을 사용한다. 우리는 long CoT reasoning (SDAR)과 short CoT instruction following (LLaDA) model 모두에서 우리의 방법을 검증한다. 표준 dLLM을 약 $\\sim$10억 token만으로 RCD paradigm으로 효율적으로 변환할 수 있음을 보인다. RCD는 다양한 benchmark 전반에서 추가 계산 오버헤드를 최소화한 상태로 frontier dLLM의 정확도를 일관되게 5--10 point 향상시킨다. 특히 가장 까다로운 AIME task에서는 RCD가 baseline 정확도를 거의 두 배로 끌어올리며, 동일한 정확도 수준에서 denoising step 수를 최대 4--5배 줄인다."},{"id":"63183","en":"Universality, Function Composition, and Algorithm Emulation All In-Context","ko":"In-Context에서의 보편성, 함수 합성, 알고리즘 에뮬레이션","authors":"Hong-Yu Chen, Po-Chiao Lin, Maojiang Su, Jerry Yao-Chieh Hu, Han Liu","pos":"#1606","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ZK0U30zmDY","abs":"<p>We study the in-context universal approximation and compositional generalization of softmax Transformers. We prove an in-context universality result:  a fixed-weight softmax Transformer  approximates a broad class of continuous sequence-to-sequence functions. Building on this universality, we establish a composition theorem: by concatenating prompts associated with simple ``subprograms,'' the same fixed Transformer executes their composition, and thereby synthesizes more complex programs on-the-fly. These results support a principled view of prompts as programs and fixed-weight Transformers as program interpreters. Moreover, we provide a concrete mechanism by which GPT-style models  both execute and assemble algorithms in context.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 softmax Transformer의 in-context universal approximation과 compositional generalization을 연구한다. 우리는 in-context universality 결과를 증명한다. 즉, 고정된 weight를 가진 softmax Transformer가 연속적인 sequence-to-sequence function의 넓은 클래스를 근사할 수 있음을 보인다. 이 universality를 바탕으로, 우리는 composition theorem을 확립한다. 즉, 단순한 ``subprograms''와 연결된 prompt를 이어 붙이면 동일한 fixed Transformer가 그들의 composition을 실행하고, 이를 통해 더 복잡한 program을 즉석에서 합성할 수 있다. 이러한 결과는 prompt를 program으로, fixed-weight Transformer를 program interpreter로 보는 원칙적인 관점을 지지한다. 더 나아가, GPT-style model이 context 안에서 algorithm을 실행하고 조립하는 구체적인 메커니즘을 제시한다.</p>"},{"id":"63454","en":"Compressed Sensing for Capability Localization in Large Language Models","ko":"대규모 언어 모델에서 능력 지역화를 위한 압축 센싱","authors":"Anna Bair, Yixuan Xu, Mingjie Sun, Zico Kolter","pos":"#2115","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=X4MFtxw1sB","abs":"Large language models (LLMs) exhibit a wide range of capabilities, including mathematical reasoning, code generation, and linguistic behaviors. We show that many capabilities are highly localized to small subsets of attention heads within Transformer architectures. Zeroing out as few as five task-specific heads can degrade performance by up to $65\\\\%$ on standard benchmarks measuring the capability of interest, while largely preserving performance on unrelated tasks. We introduce a compressed sensing based method that exploits the sparsity of these heads to identify them via strategic knockouts and a small number of model evaluations. We validate these findings across Llama and Qwen models ranging from 1B to 8B parameters and a diverse set of capabilities including mathematical abilities and code generation, revealing a modular organization in which specialized capabilities are implemented by sparse, functionally distinct components. Overall, our results suggest that capability localization is a general organizational principle of Transformer language models, with implications for interpretability, model editing, and AI safety.","absKo":"대규모 언어 모델(LLM)은 수학적 추론, 코드 생성, 언어적 행동을 포함해 매우 다양한 능력을 보인다. 우리는 이러한 많은 능력이 Transformer 아키텍처 내 attention head의 작은 부분집합에 매우 국소적으로 존재함을 보인다. 관심 있는 능력을 측정하는 표준 benchmark에서 task-specific head를 고작 다섯 개 정도만 0으로 만들어도 성능이 최대 $65\\\\%$까지 떨어질 수 있는 반면, 무관한 task의 성능은 대체로 유지된다. 우리는 이러한 head의 sparsity를 활용하는 compressed sensing 기반 방법을 제안하며, 전략적인 knockout과 소수의 모델 평가만으로 이들을 식별한다. 1B에서 8B 파라미터에 이르는 Llama와 Qwen 모델, 그리고 수학적 능력과 코드 생성을 포함한 다양한 능력 전반에서 이 결과를 검증했으며, 특화된 능력이 희소하고 기능적으로 구별되는 구성요소에 의해 구현되는 모듈식 조직을 드러낸다. 전반적으로 우리의 결과는 capability localization이 Transformer 언어 모델의 일반적인 조직 원리임을 시사하며, 이는 interpretability, model editing, AI safety에 시사점을 가진다."},{"id":"61012","en":"Chain-of-Thought Gradient Descent","ko":"Chain-of-Thought 경사 하강법","authors":"Hong-Yu Chen, Venkat Ganti, Jerry Yao-Chieh Hu, Hude Liu, Han Liu","pos":"#2211","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=uZ8JZ1Lw9a","abs":"We show that Chain-of-Thought (CoT) enables a fixed single-layer transformer to efficiently approximate the training process of an $N$-layer feed-forward network in-context.  Since FFNs are universal approximators, this result provides strong theoretical evidence for the expressive power of CoT. Specifically, we improve the computational cost of the prior best in-context result [Wu et al., ICML 2025] by $O(N)$. Building on the insight of the recursive nature of CoT, we reuse the single-layer transformer autoregressively instead of stacking the same transformer blocks to perform multiple In-Context Gradient Descent (ICGD) updates. The key novelty is a dynamic-masking scheme: at each CoT step, the attention heads are forced to see only the tokens needed to compute the result of the current forward or backpropagation update. This selective reuse contrasts with earlier ICGD proofs for neural network optimization, which must carry all information through every layer simply because a later gradient update might need it. Our numerical validations backup our theory.","absKo":"우리는 Chain-of-Thought (CoT)가 고정된 단일 레이어 transformer가 in-context에서 N-layer feed-forward network의 학습 과정을 효율적으로 근사하도록 해준다는 것을 보인다. FFN은 universal approximator이므로, 이 결과는 CoT의 표현력에 대한 강력한 이론적 근거를 제공한다. 구체적으로, 우리는 이전 최선의 in-context 결과 [Wu et al., ICML 2025]의 computational cost를 O(N)만큼 개선한다. CoT의 재귀적 성질에 대한 통찰을 바탕으로, 우리는 동일한 transformer block을 여러 번 stacking하여 여러 In-Context Gradient Descent (ICGD) 업데이트를 수행하는 대신, 단일 레이어 transformer를 autoregressive하게 재사용한다. 핵심적인 새로움은 dynamic-masking scheme이다. 각 CoT step에서 attention head는 현재 forward 또는 backpropagation update의 결과를 계산하는 데 필요한 token만 보도록 강제된다. 이러한 선택적 재사용은, 이후의 gradient update가 필요할 수도 있다는 이유만으로 모든 layer를 통해 모든 정보를 전달해야 했던 기존의 neural network optimization에 대한 ICGD 증명들과 대조적이다. 우리의 수치 검증은 이론을 뒷받침한다."},{"id":"61077","en":"Rotary Position Encodings for Graphs","ko":"그래프를 위한 Rotary Position Encoding","authors":"Isaac Reid, Arijit Sehanobish, Cederik Höfs, Bruno Mlodozeniec, Leonhard Vulpius, Federico Barbero, Adrian Weller, Krzysztof Choromanski, Richard E Turner, Petar Veličković","pos":"#2306","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=trn64znfNx","abs":"<p>We study the extent to which rotary position encodings (RoPE), a recent transformer position encoding algorithm broadly adopted in large language models (LLMs) and vision transformers (ViTs), can be applied to graph-structured data. We find that rotating tokens depending on the spectrum of the graph Laplacian efficiently injects structural information into the attention mechanism, boosting performance in synthetic and real-world graph learning tasks. This approach, coined <em>Wave-Induced Rotary Encodings</em> (WIRE), enjoys intriguing theoretical properties: it recovers regular RoPE on grids, and depends asymptotically on the graph effective resistance. Unlike bias-based relative position encodings, WIRE is compatible with linear attention.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 rotary position encoding (RoPE), 즉 large language models (LLMs)와 vision transformers (ViTs)에서 널리 채택된 최근 transformer position encoding 알고리즘이 graph-structured data에 어느 정도까지 적용될 수 있는지 연구한다. 우리는 graph Laplacian의 spectrum에 따라 token을 회전시키는 것이 attention mechanism에 구조적 정보를 효율적으로 주입하여 synthetic 및 real-world graph learning task의 성능을 향상시킨다는 것을 발견한다. <em>Wave-Induced Rotary Encodings</em> (WIRE)라 명명한 이 접근법은 흥미로운 이론적 성질을 가진다. grid에서는 regular RoPE를 복원하며, asymptotically graph effective resistance에 의존한다. bias-based relative position encoding과 달리 WIRE는 linear attention과 호환된다.</p>"},{"id":"61955","en":"TileSparse: Arithmetic-Intensity-Aware Sparse Attention for Compute-Bound LLM Decoding","ko":"TileSparse: compute-bound LLM 디코딩을 위한 연산 강도 인지형 sparse attention","authors":"Chao Wang, Pengfei Zuo, Zhangyu Chen, Qihui Zhou, Tsung-Yi Ho, Ming-Chang Yang","pos":"#2905","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=lK2AzLDJal","abs":"<p>Sparse attention has emerged as a vital technique for long-context inference in Large Language Models (LLMs), effectively accelerating memory-bound decoding by reducing memory access for non-essential keys. However, the assumption that decoding attention is memory-bound has been shattered. The proliferation of Multi-head Latent Attention (MLA) and Multi-Token Prediction (MTP) architectures has effectively rendered the process compute-bound. We observe that, in MLA, Q-heads exhibit a degree of sparsity even when attending to the same key; consequently, traditional sparse attention algorithms introduce significant computational inefficiency in this new regime by rigidly computing interactions between all associated Q-heads and the retrieved keys.  To address this, we propose TileSparse, an arithmetic-intensity-aware (a.i.-aware) algorithm for efficient attention in compute-bound settings. We first introduce a cost model that emphasizes compute budget (compute tile size) rather than memory budget (fetched tokens) when evaluating sparse methods. Next, QK 2D Sparsity prunes unnecessary Q-head--key computations and uses the freed compute to retrieve more semantically important tokens. Because Q-head sparsity differs across keys, we further propose Tiered QK 2D Sparsity and an AutoTuner to choose the best pattern. Experiments show that under tight budgets our method improves accuracy by 40% over state-of-the-art dynamic K-only sparse methods. It also preserves 99% of full-attention accuracy while cutting attention compute by 40.8%, outperforming prior sparse attention approaches.</p>","absKo":"<p>Sparse attention은 Large Language Models (LLMs)에서 long-context inference를 위한 핵심 기법으로 부상했으며, 필수적이지 않은 key에 대한 memory access를 줄임으로써 memory-bound decoding을 효과적으로 가속한다. 그러나 decoding attention이 memory-bound라는 가정은 무너졌다. Multi-head Latent Attention (MLA)와 Multi-Token Prediction (MTP) architecture의 확산은 이 과정을 사실상 compute-bound로 만들었다. 우리는 MLA에서 Q-head가 같은 key를 바라보더라도 일정 수준의 sparsity를 보인다는 점을 관찰한다. 그 결과, 전통적인 sparse attention algorithm은 관련된 모든 Q-head와 검색된 key 사이의 상호작용을 경직되게 계산함으로써, 이 새로운 regime에서 상당한 계산 비효율을 초래한다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 compute-bound setting에서 효율적인 attention을 위한 arithmetic-intensity-aware (a.i.-aware) algorithm인 TileSparse를 제안한다. 먼저 sparse method를 평가할 때 memory budget(가져온 token 수)보다 compute budget(compute tile size)에 초점을 맞춘 cost model을 도입한다. 다음으로 QK 2D Sparsity는 불필요한 Q-head--key 계산을 제거하고, 절약된 계산 자원을 더 의미적으로 중요한 token을 검색하는 데 사용한다. Q-head sparsity는 key마다 다르므로, 우리는 가장 적절한 패턴을 고르기 위해 Tiered QK 2D Sparsity와 AutoTuner를 추가로 제안한다. 실험 결과, 빡빡한 budget 하에서 우리의 방법은 state-of-the-art dynamic K-only sparse method 대비 정확도를 40% 향상시킨다. 또한 attention compute를 40.8% 줄이면서 full-attention 정확도의 99%를 유지하며, 기존 sparse attention 접근법보다 우수함을 보였다.</p>"},{"id":"61465","en":"Stochastic Sparse Attention for Memory-Bound Inference","ko":"Memory-Bound Inference를 위한 Stochastic Sparse Attention","authors":"Kyle Lee, Corentin Delacour, Kevin Callahan-Coray, Kyle Jiang, Can Yaras, Samet Oymak, Tathagata Srimani, Kerem Camsari","pos":"#2907","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ptaIjzIuoY","abs":"Autoregressive decoding becomes bandwidth-limited at long contexts, as generating each token requires reading all $n_k$ key and value vectors from KV cache. We present Stochastic Additive No-mulT Attention (SANTA), a method that sparsifies value-cache access by sampling $S \\ll n_k$ indices from the post-softmax distribution and aggregates only those value rows. This yields an unbiased estimator of the post-softmax value aggregation while replacing value-stage multiply-accumulates with gather-and-add. We introduce stratified sampling to design variance-reduced, GPU-friendly variants, demonstrating $1.5\\times$ decode-step attention kernel speedup over FlashInfer and FlashDecoding on an NVIDIA RTX 6000 Ada while matching baseline accuracy at 32k-token contexts. Finally, we propose Bernoulli $qK^\\mathsf{T}$ sampling as a complementary technique to sparsify the score stage, reducing key-feature access through stochastic ternary queries. Both methods are orthogonal to upstream techniques such as ternary quantization, low-rank projections, and KV-cache compression. Together, they point toward sparse, multiplier-free, and energy-efficient inference.","absKo":"Autoregressive decoding은 긴 context에서 bandwidth에 의해 제한되는데, 각 token을 생성할 때 KV cache에서 모든 $n_k$개의 key와 value vector를 읽어와야 하기 때문이다. 우리는 Stochastic Additive No-mulT Attention (SANTA)를 제시한다. 이 방법은 post-softmax distribution에서 $S \\ll n_k$개의 index를 sampling하여 value-cache access를 sparsify하고, 해당 value row만을 집계한다. 이는 post-softmax value aggregation의 unbiased estimator를 제공하면서, value-stage의 multiply-accumulate를 gather-and-add로 대체한다. 우리는 variance를 줄이고 GPU 친화적인 variant를 설계하기 위해 stratified sampling을 도입하며, NVIDIA RTX 6000 Ada에서 FlashInfer 및 FlashDecoding 대비 decode-step attention kernel speedup이 1.5\\times에 달하면서도 32k-token context에서 baseline accuracy와 일치함을 보인다. 마지막으로, score stage를 sparsify하기 위한 보완적 기법으로 Bernoulli $qK^\\mathsf{T}$ sampling을 제안하여 stochastic ternary query를 통해 key-feature access를 줄인다. 두 방법은 ternary quantization, low-rank projection, KV-cache compression과 같은 상위 기법들과 서로 직교적이다. 이들을 종합하면 sparse하고, multiplier-free이며, energy-efficient inference를 향한 방향을 제시한다."},{"id":"65957","en":"Stem: Rethinking Causal Information Flow in Sparse Attention","ko":"Stem: 희소 Attention에서의 인과적 정보 흐름 재고","authors":"Lin Niu, Xin Luo, LinchuanXie, Yifu Sun, Guanghua Yu, Jianchen Zhu, S Kevin Zhou","pos":"#2908","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=8WrMPCd7Kr","abs":"The quadratic computational complexity of self-attention remains a fundamental bottleneck for scaling Large Language Models (LLMs) to long contexts, particularly during the pre-filling phase. In this paper, we rethink the causal attention mechanism from the perspective of information flow. Due to causal constraints, tokens at initial positions participate in the aggregation of every subsequent token. However, existing sparse methods typically apply a uniform top-$k$ selection across all token positions within a layer, ignoring the cumulative dependency of token information inherent in causal architectures. To address this, we propose Stem, a novel, plug-and-play sparsity module aligned with information flow. First, Stem employs the Token Position-Decay strategy, applying position-dependent top-$k$ within each layer to retain initial tokens for recursive dependencies. Second, to preserve information-rich tokens, Stem utilizes the Output-Aware Metric. It prioritizes high-impact tokens based on approximate output magnitude.  Extensive evaluations demonstrate that Stem achieves superior accuracy with reduced computation and pre-filling latency. Code is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/stem-254ENLXL."},{"id":"66195","en":"Sparser Block-Sparse Attention via Token Permutation","ko":"토큰 순열을 통한 더 희소한 Block-Sparse Attention","authors":"Xinghao Wang, Pengyu Wang, Dong Zhang, Chenkun Tan, Shaojun Zhou, Zhaoxiang Liu, Shiguo Lian, Fangxu Liu, Kai Song, Xipeng Qiu","pos":"#2909","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=5u3Ra6Qf5C","abs":"Scaling the context length of large language models (LLMs) offers significant benefits but is computationally expensive. This expense stems primarily from the self-attention mechanism, whose $O(N^2)$ complexity with respect to sequence length presents a major bottleneck for both memory and latency. Fortunately, the attention matrix is often sparse, particularly for long sequences, suggesting an opportunity for optimization. Block-sparse attention has emerged as a promising solution that partitions sequences into blocks and skips computation for a subset of these blocks. However, the effectiveness of this method is highly dependent on the underlying attention patterns, which can lead to sub-optimal block-level sparsity. For instance, important key tokens for queries within a single block may be scattered across numerous other blocks, leading to computational redundancy. In this work, we propose Permuted Block-Sparse Attention (**PBS-Attn**), a plug-and-play method that leverages the permutation properties of attention to increase block-level sparsity and enhance the computational efficiency of LLM prefilling. We conduct comprehensive experiments on challenging long-context datasets, demonstrating that PBS-Attn consistently outperforms existing block-sparse attention methods in model accuracy and closely matches the full attention baseline. Powered by our custom permuted-FlashAttention kernels, PBS-Attn achieves an end-to-end speedup of up to $\\mathbf{2.75\\times}$ in long-context prefilling, confirming its practical viability. Code available at \\url{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/pbs-attn-BB66}."},{"id":"65096","en":"Scalable Medical Multimodal Fusion via Symmetric Consistency Modeling","ko":"대칭 일관성 모델링을 통한 확장 가능한 의료 멀티모달 융합","authors":"Xiaowen Sun, Hui Liu, Gongguan Chen, Ning Mao","pos":"#2910","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=GoggYknNdN","abs":"<p>Medical diagnosis tasks often rely on heterogeneous information from multiple sources, such as medical images and clinical text. Multimodal fusion is therefore essential for improving classification performance and robustness. However, most existing methods assume a fixed and known modality set, making them less effective when the number or composition of modalities changes. To address this limitation, we propose a modality-agnostic medical multimodal fusion framework that can naturally accommodate an arbitrary number of input modalities. At the coarse-grained modality level, we represent each modality’s estimation of latent semantics as an uncertainty-aware probability distribution, and impose symmetric consistency constraints to achieve global cross-modal semantic alignment. At the fine-grained token level, we further design a token-level consistency constraint based on linear reconstruction. This constraint enables structured mutual verification of local semantics across modalities. Finally, for multimodal fusion, we adopt a multi-view consistency strategy to obtain a unified representation for diagnosis prediction. In particular, each modality is sequentially treated as a conditional view to suppress noise in the remaining modalities and extract shared semantics. Extensive experiments on five public and self-constructed multimodal medical datasets demonstrate the effectiveness and scalability of the proposed approach. Code is available at https://github.com/gjhgjbkg/SMMF.</p>"},{"id":"62978","en":"RAT+: Train Dense, Infer Sparse - Recurrence Augmented Attention for Dilated Inference","ko":"RAT+: Train Dense, Infer Sparse - Dilated Inference를 위한 Recurrence Augmented Attention","authors":"Xiuying Wei, Caglar Gulcehre","pos":"#2911","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=bIF47tRlP4","abs":"Structured dilated attention has an appealing inference-time efficiency knob: it reduces the FLOPs of the attention and the KV cache size by a factor of the dilation size $\\mathtt{D}$, while preserving long-range connectivity. However, we find a persistent failure mode of them -sparsifying a pretrained attention model to a dilated pattern leads to severe accuracy degradation. We introduce **RAT+**, a dense-pretraining architecture that augments attention with *full-sequence recurrence* and *active recurrence learning*. A single RAT+ model is pretrained densely once, then flexibly switched at inference time to dilated attention (optionally with local windows) or hybrid layer/head compositions, requiring only a short 1B-token resolution adaptation rather than retraining separate sparse models. At 1.5B parameters trained on 100B tokens, RAT+ closely matches dense accuracy at $\\mathtt{D=16}$ and drops by about 2-3 points at $\\mathtt{D=64}$ on commonsense reasoning and LongBench tasks, respectively. Moreover, RAT+ outperforms attention when sparsifying to the top-k block attention. We further scale to 2.6B parameters and 200B tokens and observe the same trend.","absKo":"Structured dilated attention은 매력적인 inference-time 효율 조절 수단을 제공합니다. dilation size의 factor인 $\\mathtt{D}$만큼 attention의 FLOPs와 KV cache 크기를 줄이면서도 long-range connectivity는 유지하기 때문입니다. 그러나 우리는 이 방식의 지속적인 failure mode를 발견했습니다. pretrained attention model을 dilated pattern으로 sparsify하면 심각한 정확도 저하가 발생합니다. 우리는 attention에 *full-sequence recurrence*와 *active recurrence learning*을 추가하는 dense-pretraining architecture인 **RAT+**를 소개합니다. 하나의 RAT+ model은 한 번 dense하게 pretraining된 뒤, inference 시점에 dilated attention(선택적으로 local window 포함) 또는 hybrid layer/head composition으로 유연하게 전환할 수 있으며, 별도의 sparse model을 다시 학습하는 대신 짧은 1B-token resolution adaptation만 필요합니다. 100B token으로 학습한 1.5B parameter 설정에서 RAT+는 $\\mathtt{D=16}$에서 dense accuracy에 근접하고, commonsense reasoning과 LongBench task에서 각각 약 2-3 point 하락에 그칩니다. 또한 RAT+는 top-k block attention으로 sparsify할 때 attention보다 우수합니다. 우리는 이를 2.6B parameter와 200B token으로 더 확장했으며 동일한 경향을 관찰했습니다."},{"id":"64387","en":"Q-Delta: Beyond Key–Value Associative State Evolution","ko":"Q-Delta: 키-값 연상 상태 진화를 넘어","authors":"Sumin Park, Seojin Kim, Noseong Park","pos":"#2912","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=O6tuJZIv0u","abs":"<p>Linear attention reformulates sequence modeling as recurrent state evolution, enabling efficient linear-time inference.  Under the key–value associative paradigm, existing approaches restrict the role of the query to the readout operation, decoupling it from state evolution. We show that query-conditioned state readout induces a structured value prediction over accumulated memory that complements key-based retrieval. Based on this insight, we propose Q-Delta, a query-aware delta rule that integrates mixed key--query prediction errors into state evolution, enabling jointly corrective dynamics while preserving delta-rule efficiency. We establish stability guarantees for the resulting dynamics and derive a hardware-efficient chunkwise-parallel formulation with a custom Triton implementation. Empirical results demonstrate stable optimization, competitive throughput, and consistent improvements over strong baselines on language modeling and long-context retrieval tasks.</p>","absKo":"<p>Linear attention은 sequence modeling을 recurrent state evolution으로 재구성하여 효율적인 linear-time inference를 가능하게 한다. key-value associative paradigm 하에서 기존 접근법은 query의 역할을 readout operation에 제한하여 state evolution과 분리한다. 우리는 query-conditioned state readout이 축적된 memory 위에서 구조화된 value prediction을 유도하며, 이는 key-based retrieval을 보완함을 보인다. 이 통찰을 바탕으로 우리는 Q-Delta를 제안한다. Q-Delta는 mixed key--query prediction error를 state evolution에 통합하는 query-aware delta rule로, delta-rule 효율성을 유지하면서 joint corrective dynamics를 가능하게 한다. 우리는 이러한 dynamics에 대한 안정성 보장을 확립하고, custom Triton implementation을 갖춘 hardware-efficient chunkwise-parallel formulation을 유도한다. 실험 결과는 language modeling과 long-context retrieval task에서 강력한 baseline 대비 안정적인 최적화, 경쟁력 있는 throughput, 그리고 일관된 성능 향상을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"65364","en":"Prototype Transformer: Towards Language Model Architectures Interpretable by Design","ko":"Prototype Transformer: 설계상 해석 가능한 언어 모델 아키텍처를 향하여","authors":"Yordan Yordanov, Matteo Forasassi, Bayar Menzat, Tommaso Salvatori, Ruizhi Wang, Markus Kaltenberger, Amine M&amp;#x27;Charrak, Chang Qi, Thomas Lukasiewicz","pos":"#2913","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ELiOhFJIPh","abs":"<p>While state-of-the-art language models (LMs) surpass the vast majority of humans in certain domains, their reasoning remains largely opaque, reducing trust and risking deception and hallucination. In this work, we introduce the Prototype Transformer (ProtoT)—an autoregressive LM architecture that replaces the quadratic-cost self-attention in the transformer with a linear-cost module based on prototypes (parameter vectors). In ProtoT, the prototypes create communication channels aggregating contextual information at different time scales. We show that this leads to the prototypes automatically capturing nameable concepts (e.g.  “woman”) during training, and it provides the potential to interpret the model’s reasoning and do targeted edits of its behavior. Compared to baselines, ProtoT scales well with model and data size, shows robustness to input perturbations, and performs well on text generation and downstream tasks (GLUE). Reaching close to the performance of state-of-the-art architectures, ProtoT paves the way to creating well-performing autoregressive LMs interpretable by design.</p>"},{"id":"63882","en":"Prism: Spectral-Aware Block-Sparse Attention","ko":"Prism: 스펙트럼 인지 블록 희소 attention","authors":"Xinghao Wang, Pengyu Wang, Xiaoran Liu, Fangxu Liu, Jason Chu, Kai Song, Xipeng Qiu","pos":"#2914","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=SpQABsjB9Y","abs":"Block-sparse attention is promising for accelerating long-context LLM pre-filling, yet identifying relevant blocks efficiently remains a bottleneck. Existing methods typically employ coarse-grained attention as a proxy for block importance estimation, but often resort to expensive token-level searching or scoring, resulting in significant selection overhead. In this work, we trace the inaccuracy of standard coarse-grained attention via mean pooling to a theoretical root cause: the interaction between mean pooling and Rotary Positional Embeddings (RoPE). We prove that mean pooling acts as a low-pass filter that induces destructive interference in high-frequency dimensions, effectively creating a \"blind spot\" for local positional information (e.g., slash patterns). To address this, we introduce Prism, a training-free spectral-aware approach that decomposes block selection into high-frequency and low-frequency branches.  By applying energy-based temperature calibration, Prism restores the attenuated positional signals directly from pooled representations, enabling block importance estimation using purely block-level operations, thereby improving efficiency. Extensive evaluations confirm that Prism maintains accuracy parity with full attention while delivering up to $\\mathbf{5.1\\times}$ speedup. Code available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/prism_anonymous-7E36.","absKo":"Block-sparse attention은 긴 context의 LLM pre-filling을 가속하는 데 유망하지만, 관련 있는 block을 효율적으로 식별하는 것이 병목이다. 기존 방법은 일반적으로 block 중요도 추정을 위한 proxy로 coarse-grained attention을 사용하지만, token-level searching이나 scoring을 비용 많이 드는 방식으로 수행하는 경우가 많아 selection overhead가 크다. 본 연구에서는 mean pooling을 통한 standard coarse-grained attention의 부정확성을 이론적 근본 원인, 즉 mean pooling과 Rotary Positional Embeddings (RoPE)의 상호작용으로 추적한다. 우리는 mean pooling이 high-frequency dimension에서 destructive interference를 유발하는 low-pass filter로 작동하여 local positional information(예: slash pattern)에 대한 \"blind spot\"을 사실상 만든다는 것을 증명한다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 block selection을 high-frequency branch와 low-frequency branch로 분해하는 training-free spectral-aware 접근법 Prism을 제안한다. energy-based temperature calibration을 적용함으로써, Prism은 pooled representation에서 attenuated positional signal을 직접 복원하여 순수하게 block-level operation만으로 block 중요도를 추정할 수 있게 하며, 이에 따라 효율성을 향상시킨다. 대규모 평가 결과 Prism은 full attention과 동등한 정확도를 유지하면서 최대 $\\mathbf{5.1\\times}$의 속도 향상을 제공함을 확인했다. 코드는 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/prism_anonymous-7E36 에서 확인할 수 있다."},{"id":"63733","en":"Preconditioned DeltaNet: Curvature-aware Sequence Modeling for Linear Recurrences","ko":"Preconditioned DeltaNet: 선형 재귀를 위한 곡률 인지 시퀀스 모델링","authors":"Neehal Tumma, Noel Loo, Daniela Rus","pos":"#2915","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=UC6YiTOeKb","abs":"<p>To address the increasing long-context compute limitations of softmax attention, several subquadratic recurrent operators have been developed. This work includes models such as Mamba-2, DeltaNet, Gated DeltaNet (GDN), and Kimi Delta Attention (KDA). As the space of recurrences grows, a parallel line of work has arisen to taxonomize them. One compelling view is the test-time regression (TTR) framework, which interprets recurrences as performing online least squares updates that learn a linear map from the keys to values. Existing delta-rule recurrences can be seen as first-order approximations to this objective, but notably ignore the curvature of the least-squares loss during optimization. In this work, we address this by introducing preconditioning to these recurrences. Starting from the theory of online least squares, we derive equivalences between linear attention and the delta rule in the exactly preconditioned case. Next, we realize this theory in practice by proposing a diagonal approximation: this enables us to introduce preconditioned variants of DeltaNet, GDN, and KDA alongside efficient chunkwise parallel algorithms for computing them. Empirically, we find that our preconditioned delta-rule recurrences yield consistent performance improvements across synthetic recall benchmarks and language modeling at the 340M and 1B scale.</p>","absKo":"<p>softmax attention의 장기 context 계산 한계를 해결하기 위해, 여러 subquadratic recurrent operator가 개발되어 왔다. 이 연구에는 Mamba-2, DeltaNet, Gated DeltaNet (GDN), Kimi Delta Attention (KDA)와 같은 model이 포함된다. recurrence 공간이 커지면서, 이를 범주화하려는 parallel한 연구 흐름도 등장했다. 특히 매력적인 관점 중 하나는 test-time regression (TTR) framework로, recurrence를 key에서 value로 가는 linear map을 학습하는 online least squares update로 해석한다. 기존 delta-rule recurrence는 이 목적함수의 first-order approximation으로 볼 수 있지만, 최적화 중 least-squares loss의 curvature를 주목할 만하게도 무시한다. 본 연구에서는 preconditioning을 이러한 recurrence에 도입하여 이를 해결한다. online least squares 이론에서 출발해, 우리는 정확히 preconditioned 된 경우 linear attention과 delta rule 사이의 등가를 유도한다. 다음으로, 우리는 diagonal approximation을 제안하여 이 이론을 실제로 구현한다. 이를 통해 DeltaNet, GDN, KDA의 preconditioned variant를 효율적인 chunkwise parallel algorithm과 함께 계산할 수 있게 한다. 실증적으로, 우리의 preconditioned delta-rule recurrence는 합성 recall benchmark와 340M 및 1B 규모의 language modeling에서 일관된 성능 향상을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"65762","en":"Not All Answers Are Contextually Persuadable: Inference Dynamics in Large Language Models under Contextual Influence","ko":"모든 답이 문맥적으로 설득 가능한 것은 아니다: 문맥적 영향 하에서 대형 언어 모델의 추론 동역학","authors":"Zongye Hu, Weiqing Luo, Yanjie Fu, Yu Gan, Haofeng Zhang, Ziyi Huang","pos":"#2916","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=APjCfbJiJr","abs":"<p>At the core of modern prompting techniques is contextual sensitivity, the ability of large language models to adapt their predictions based on inference-time context. Despite its central role, inference behavior under strong contextual influence remains poorly understood, particularly at the level of internal inference dynamics. To bridge this gap, we introduce a theoretical framework for analyzing contextual influence through inference dynamics, enabling quantitative characterization of inference behavior beyond output-level answer changes. Our analysis shows that inference dynamics do not exhibit unbounded drift under repeated contextual assertions. Instead, predictive representations converge to stable, query-dependent regimes that fundamentally constrain whether contextual signals can alter a model’s prediction. This leads to a surprising finding: Repeated contextual assertions do not act as accumulating evidence during inference and may therefore fail to alter a model’s prediction even under unbounded repetition, while in other cases a prediction change becomes inevitable. We empirically validate our theoretical predictions across diverse models and tasks, demonstrating strong alignment between theory and observed inference behavior. These contributions offer a principled pathway toward characterizing the limits of contextual influence during inference, and provide practical implications for designing and evaluating repetition-based prompting methods.</p>"},{"id":"64821","en":"A Provable Expressiveness Hierarchy in Hybrid Linear-Full Attention","ko":"Hybrid Linear-Full Attention에서 증명 가능한 표현력 계층","authors":"Xiaowei Ye, Xiaoyu He, Chao Liao, Chen Wu, Pinyan Lu","pos":"#3004","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=JPnA2BI6U5","abs":"Transformers serve as the foundation of most modern large language models.  To mitigate the quadratic complexity of standard full attention, various efficient attention mechanisms, such as linear and hybrid attention, have been developed.  A fundamental gap remains: their expressive power relative to full attention lacks a rigorous theoretical characterization.  In this work, we theoretically characterize the performance differences among these attention mechanisms.  Our theory applies to all linear attention variants that can be formulated as a recurrence, including Mamba, DeltaNet, etc.  Specifically, we establish an expressiveness hierarchy: for the sequential function composition-a multi-step reasoning task that must occur within a model’s forward pass, an $(L+1)$-layer full attention network is sufficient, whereas any hybrid network interleaving $L-1$ layers of full attention with a substantially larger number ($2^{3L^2}$) of linear attention layers cannot solve it.  This result demonstrates a clear separation in expressive power between the two types of attention.  Our work provides the first provable separation between hybrid attention and standard full attention, offering a theoretical perspective for understanding the fundamental capabilities and limitations of different attention mechanisms."},{"id":"66106","en":"Attention with Routed-Memory for Learnable Sparse Control","ko":"학습 가능한 희소 제어를 위한 라우팅 메모리 Attention","authors":"QIUHAO Zeng, Jerry Huang, Peng Lu, Ruiyi Fang, Gezheng Xu, Zihao Jing, Yufei Cui, Charles X. Ling, Gang Niu, Boyu Wang","pos":"#3005","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=6zbO21ySVJ","abs":"<p>Despite advances in long-context inference, large language models (LLMs) remain fundamentally limited by the key-value (KV) caching mechanisms that are necessary for stable computation. Management techniques, such as selective token eviction and pruning, have vastly mitigated the issues that have arisen, but often discard potentially useful information to manage the growing memory requirements of the cache. In this paper, we build upon these approaches to propose Attention with Routed Memory ARM, a novel KV caching structure that introduces a fully differentiable, fixed-size memory system organized as a hierarchical routing structure that learns to select memory slots via Gumbel-Softmax and performs sigmoid-gated updates that softly combine new and stored information, avoiding hard eviction and thereby reducing information loss. By combining this with a policy to dynamically select varying amounts of memory at inference, ARM adapts its accesses for simple contexts and expanding retrieval for inputs that require deeper reasoning, enabling more scalable and effective retrieval on both short and long contexts. Experimental results on standard commonsense and long-context reasoning benchmarks demonstrate that ARM achieves superior performance and efficiency compared to fixed KV-caching approaches, while remaining efficient and scalable in terms of both memory and generation latency.</p>"},{"id":"60893","en":"EchoAttention: Exploiting Token-Pair Redundancy and Frame-Block Similarity for Efficient Long Video Generation","ko":"EchoAttention: 효율적인 Long Video Generation을 위한 Token-Pair 중복성과 Frame-Block 유사성 활용","authors":"Yifei Xia, Fangcheng Fu, Hao Yuan, Suhan Ling, Xupeng Miao, Huixia Li, Yuxi Ren, Xin Xia, Xuefeng Xiao, Bin Cui","pos":"#3006","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=vZZUCDcjSx","abs":"Diffusion Transformers (DiTs) are increasingly adopted for long-video generation, yet inference is dominated by the quadratic cost of 3D full attention. Sparse attention mitigates this bottleneck by exploiting *token-pair redundancy* and pruning query-key interactions.  Nevertheless, its effectiveness on long video generation is often constrained by non-sparse attention heads, making it hard to strike a good balance between inference speed and generation quality. To address this, we identify another pervasive but overlooked redundancy specific to video DiTs: *frame-block similarity*, where frame-blocks in attention weights exhibit highly similar distributions and can be well approximated by lightweight linear calibration. Motivated by this observation, we propose **EchoAttention**, which jointly leverages *token-pair redundancy* (*Sparse* operator) and *frame-block similarity* (*Echo* operator), together with a fine-grained routing policy learned via three-stage distillation. This design enables efficient handling of both sparse and non-sparse heads, overcoming the inherent ceiling of purely sparse attention and yielding a better speed-quality trade-off. Across public video DiTs, EchoAttention consistently improves the speed-quality frontier over SOTA sparse-attention baselines, reducing end-to-end latency up to 2.42$\\times$ with minimal quality loss.","absKo":"Diffusion Transformer(DiT)는 long-video generation에 점점 더 널리 채택되고 있지만, 추론은 3D full attention의 quadratic cost에 의해 지배된다. sparse attention은 token-pair redundancy를 활용하고 query-key interaction을 pruning함으로써 이 병목을 완화한다. 그러나 long video generation에서의 효과는 non-sparse attention head 때문에 종종 제한되며, 그 결과 inference speed와 generation quality 사이의 좋은 균형을 맞추기 어렵다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 video DiT에 특화되어 있으면서도 널리 간과되었던 또 하나의 redundancy인 frame-block similarity를 식별한다. 이는 attention weight의 frame-block들이 매우 유사한 분포를 보이며, 가벼운 linear calibration으로 충분히 근사될 수 있다는 것이다. 이러한 관찰에 동기를 얻어, 우리는 token-pair redundancy를 활용하는 Sparse operator와 frame-block similarity를 활용하는 Echo operator를 결합하고, 세 단계 distillation으로 학습된 fine-grained routing policy를 함께 사용하는 **EchoAttention**을 제안한다. 이 설계는 sparse head와 non-sparse head를 모두 효율적으로 처리할 수 있게 하여, 순수 sparse attention의 본질적 한계를 넘어 더 나은 speed-quality trade-off를 제공한다. 공개 video DiT 전반에서 EchoAttention은 SOTA sparse-attention baseline보다 speed-quality frontier를 일관되게 개선하며, 최소한의 quality loss로 end-to-end latency를 최대 2.42$\\times$까지 줄인다.</p>"},{"id":"60639","en":"Faster Query-Key Learning Sharpens Attention in Self-Attention Models","ko":"더 빠른 Query-Key 학습은 Self-Attention Model의 Attention을 선명하게 한다","authors":"Rahul Vashisht, Harish Ramaswamy","pos":"#3007","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=yESGs2JgSu","abs":"<p>A standard self-attention layer consists of two interacting circuits: the query-key circuit that governs attention allocation, and the output-value circuit that maps attended representations to predictions. Collapsed and factorized parameterizations of the query-key and output-value circuits lead to qualitatively different attention patterns. In particular, some parameterizations give sharper attention to task-relevant tokens, at a similar training loss. We analyze how the parameterizations of these circuits shape the parameter trajectories in single-layer self-attention models trained on next-token prediction. Through gradient-flow analysis, we show that factorization induces implicit rescaling of the two circuits' learning rates. We derive closed-form dynamics showing that output-value and query-key parameters move along a line, with relative speeds determined by their learning rates. Faster query-key learning relative to output-value learning thus produces sharper attention, as the model compensates for slower output-value learning by increasing attention mass on relevant tokens. Experiments show that differences in the relative learning rates of the two circuits govern attention concentration. This improves attention interpretability while maintaining comparable predictive performance.</p>","absKo":"<p>표준 self-attention layer는 두 개의 상호작용하는 circuit으로 구성된다. attention allocation을 제어하는 query-key circuit과, attended representation을 prediction으로 매핑하는 output-value circuit이다. query-key와 output-value circuit의 collapsed 및 factorized parameterization은 qualitatively 다른 attention pattern을 만든다. 특히 일부 parameterization은 비슷한 training loss에서도 task-relevant token에 더 sharp한 attention을 부여한다. 우리는 next-token prediction으로 학습된 single-layer self-attention model에서 이러한 circuit의 parameterization이 parameter trajectory를 어떻게 형성하는지 분석한다. gradient-flow analysis를 통해, factorization이 두 circuit의 learning rate에 implicit rescaling을 유도함을 보인다. 우리는 output-value parameter와 query-key parameter가 한 직선을 따라 움직이며, 상대적 속도는 learning rate에 의해 결정된다는 closed-form dynamics를 도출한다. 따라서 query-key learning이 output-value learning보다 빠를수록, 모델은 더 느린 output-value learning을 보상하기 위해 관련 token에 더 많은 attention mass를 부여하므로 더 sharp한 attention이 나타난다. 실험은 두 circuit의 상대적 learning rate 차이가 attention concentration을 지배함을 보여준다. 이는 유사한 predictive performance를 유지하면서 attention interpretability를 향상시킨다.</p>"},{"id":"61344","en":"Faster Than Flash: Exploiting Attention Sparsity for Efficient Long-Context Decoding","ko":"Faster Than Flash: 효율적 Long-Context Decoding을 위한 Attention 희소성 활용","authors":"Zhigeng Liu, Zhiyuan Ning, Ruixiao Li, Xiaoran Liu, Yuerong Song, Min zhang, Ziwei He, Xipeng Qiu","pos":"#3008","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=r8YhlMRUR2","abs":"The development of long-context Large Language Models (LLMs) is constrained by the memory bandwidth bottleneck and quadratic complexity of the attention mechanism during decoding. To overcome the inherent trade-offs between the memory overhead of metadata-based metrics and the computational inefficiency of adaptive selection strategies, we present \\textbf{Faster Flash Decoding (FFD)}, a novel hardware-algorithm co-design framework designed to break the memory wall in long-context decoding. FFD integrates the selector and computer into a fully fused kernel, replacing external metadata indices with content-aware scanning via low-bit quantization. Furthermore, we introduce the top-$\\delta$ strategy, which dynamically filters blocks to achieve distribution-adaptive sparsity without global synchronization. As a training-free, plug-and-play solution, FFD enables the reuse of scanning results for computation, achieving up to 11.6x kernel-level speedup at 256k context length and 2.37x end-to-end throughput improvement. Empirical validation on Ruler and Longbench confirms that FFD maintains model accuracy while delivering high-ratio sparsity.","absKo":"long-context Large Language Models (LLMs)의 개발은 decoding 동안의 attention mechanism이 가지는 memory bandwidth 병목과 quadratic complexity에 의해 제약된다. metadata-based metric의 메모리 오버헤드와 adaptive selection strategy의 계산 비효율 사이의 본질적 trade-off를 극복하기 위해, 우리는 long-context decoding에서 memory wall을 허물도록 설계된 새로운 hardware-algorithm co-design 프레임워크인 \\textbf{Faster Flash Decoding (FFD)}를 제안한다. FFD는 selector와 computer를 완전히 fused된 kernel 하나로 통합하며, 외부 metadata index를 low-bit quantization을 이용한 content-aware scanning으로 대체한다. 나아가, 우리는 global synchronization 없이 distribution-adaptive sparsity를 달성하기 위해 블록을 동적으로 필터링하는 top-$\\delta$ strategy를 도입한다. training-free plug-and-play 해법으로서, FFD는 scanning 결과를 computation에 재사용할 수 있게 하며, 256k context length에서 kernel-level speedup 최대 11.6x, end-to-end throughput 2.37x 향상을 달성한다. Ruler와 Longbench에서의 실증 검증은 FFD가 높은 비율의 sparsity를 제공하면서도 모델 정확도를 유지함을 확인한다."},{"id":"63473","en":"FiX: Introducing Fine-grained Forget Gate into Softmax Attention","ko":"FiX: Softmax 어텐션에 세밀한 Forget Gate 도입","authors":"Runzhong Li, Renjie Liu, Qing Li, Bo Tang","pos":"#3009","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=WsNpCXq6SG","abs":"<p>Causal softmax attention is the algorithmic foundation of modern large language models. Inspired by linear attention, recent work has sought to enhance it by incorporating forget gates. However, these efforts, such as FoX, have been limited to coarse, scalar gates. While fine-grained, element-wise gates are shown to be more effective than scalar ones in linear attention, their direct integration into softmax attention is non-trivial due to algebraic constraints. In this work, we introduce <em>Fine-grained Forgetting Transformer</em> (<em>FiX</em>), a novel architecture that successfully enables element-wise forget gates in softmax attention. Our core insight is that the softmax denominator becomes mathematically redundant under a subsequent RMSNorm layer, allowing us to reformulate the forgetting mechanism as a direct element-wise multiplication on the value vectors. This formulation makes FiX the first positional encoding applied to value-output (VO) pairs, designed to be complementary to existing query-key (QK) encodings like RoPE. We systematically address implementation challenges including numerical precision, computational efficiency, and inference memory consumption. Extensive experiments show <em>FiX</em> achieves lower training loss and superior performance on both short-text common sense benchmarks and long-context tasks, opening a new path for building more powerful transformers.</p>","absKo":"<p>Causal softmax attention은 현대 large language model의 알고리즘적 기반이다. linear attention에서 영감을 받아, 최근 연구들은 forget gate를 통합함으로써 이를 강화하고자 했다. 그러나 FoX와 같은 이러한 시도는 coarse한 scalar gate에만 한정되어 있었다. linear attention에서는 fine-grained한 element-wise gate가 scalar gate보다 더 효과적임이 보였지만, algebraic constraint 때문에 이를 softmax attention에 직접 통합하는 것은 자명하지 않다. 본 연구에서는 element-wise forget gate를 softmax attention에서 성공적으로 가능하게 하는 새로운 architecture인 <em>Fine-grained Forgetting Transformer</em> (<em>FiX</em>)를 제안한다. 우리의 핵심 통찰은 후속 RMSNorm layer 아래에서 softmax denominator가 수학적으로 중복적이 된다는 점이며, 이를 통해 forgetting mechanism을 value vector에 대한 직접적인 element-wise multiplication으로 재정식화할 수 있다. 이 formulation은 FiX를 value-output (VO) pair에 적용되는 최초의 positional encoding으로 만들며, RoPE와 같은 기존의 query-key (QK) encoding과 상보적으로 설계되었다. 우리는 numerical precision, computational efficiency, inference memory consumption을 포함한 구현상의 도전을 체계적으로 다룬다. 광범위한 실험은 <em>FiX</em>가 더 낮은 training loss와 short-text common sense benchmark 및 long-context task 모두에서 더 우수한 성능을 달성함을 보여주며, 더 강력한 transformer를 구축하기 위한 새로운 경로를 연다.</p>"},{"id":"64720","en":"From Pairwise Affinities to Functional Correspondences: Rethinking Attention","ko":"Pairwise Affinity에서 Functional Correspondence로: Attention 재고","authors":"Jiefang Xiao, Maolin Gao, Simon Weber, Guandao Yang, Daniel Cremers","pos":"#3011","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=KWlraRUdwI","abs":"<p>Learning mappings between infinite-dimensional function spaces, or operator learning, is essential for many machine learning applications. Although transformer-based operators are popular, they often rely on token-wise attention. These methods treat continuous fields as discrete tokens and usually ignore the global functional structure.  We introduce {Functional Attention}, which reinterprets attention as a functional correspondence between adaptive bases. Inspired by geometric functional maps, our method replaces softmax affinities with structured linear operators. This yields a compact, generalizable, resolution-invariant representation that explicitly captures global dependencies.  Experiments demonstrate that {Functional Attention} can match state-of-the-art performance in many operator learning tasks, including solving PDEs, 3D segmentation, and regression, while remaining robust to varying discretizations.</p>","absKo":"<p>무한 차원 함수 공간 사이의 mapping을 학습하는 것, 즉 operator learning은 많은 machine learning 응용에서 필수적이다. transformer 기반 operator가 널리 쓰이지만, 종종 token-wise attention에 의존한다. 이러한 방법은 연속적인 field를 이산 token으로 취급하며, 대개 전역적 함수 구조를 무시한다. 우리는 attention을 적응적 basis 간의 functional correspondence로 재해석하는 {Functional Attention}을 제안한다. geometric functional map에서 영감을 받은 우리의 방법은 softmax affinity를 structured linear operator로 대체한다. 이를 통해 전역적 의존성을 명시적으로 포착하는, 작고 일반화 가능하며 해상도 불변적인 representation을 얻는다. 실험은 {Functional Attention}이 PDE 해결, 3D segmentation, regression을 포함한 많은 operator learning task에서 다양한 discretization에 대해 견고함을 유지하면서 최신 성능에 필적할 수 있음을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"64876","en":"Hamiltonian Asymmetric Fusion: One-Way Safe Directed Refinement under Modality Imbalance","ko":"Hamiltonian 비대칭 Fusion: Modality 불균형 하의 One-Way 안전 지향 정제","authors":"Bingbing Chen, Congcong Liu, Dong Liang, Zhuo-Xu Cui","pos":"#3012","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Iv8D6q1gQL","abs":"<p>Multimodal fusion is commonly implemented via symmetric token interaction, implicitly allowing information to flow in both directions. Under <em>modality imbalance</em>---when an auxiliary stream is substantially noisier than a designated primary stream---such symmetry creates a <em>backflow channel</em> that injects auxiliary noise into the primary representation and amplifies errors across iterative refinement stages. We formulate fusion in this regime as <em>directed refinement with one-way safety</em>: the primary modality defines a guidance field, while only auxiliary representations are iteratively purified, and primary perturbations induced by the auxiliary stream are explicitly bounded. We propose <em>Hamiltonian Asymmetric Fusion</em> (HAF), a lightweight unrolled refinement block that updates auxiliary tokens with momentum regularization and gated driving. The refinement force is instantiated by FFT-based spectral global correlation and modulated by a shared learnable spectral response to emphasize reliable frequency components with minimal parameters; a leaky momentum gate and a stable integrator improve multi-step refinement stability. We provide guarantees of auxiliary error contraction and bounded primary perturbation, which symmetric fusion operators do not satisfy under imbalance. Experiments on six RGB--D SOD benchmarks show consistent gains and substantially more graceful degradation under controlled auxiliary corruption.</p>"},{"id":"65658","en":"Induction Heads Interpolate N-Grams","ko":"Induction Head는 N-Gram을 보간한다","authors":"Francesco D&amp;#x27;Angelo, Oğuz Yüksel, Swathi Narashiman, Nicolas Flammarion","pos":"#3013","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=BSY7jhBxM1","abs":"Induction heads are attention circuits believed to underlie in-context learning in transformers, yet a precise characterization of the estimators they implement remains elusive. We study transformers trained on order-$k$ Markov chains and prove that a two-layer disentangled transformer implements a soft context-matching estimator that aggregates contributions from all partial context matches, weighted exponentially by their degree of overlap. This mechanism admits two complementary smoothing interpretations. First, prepending a beginning-of-sequence (BOS) token induces additive pseudo-counts, recovering Dirichlet-style smoothing. Second, a finite attention temperature enables interpolation across context orders, analogous to Jelinek–Mercer smoothing but with data-dependent weights that adapt to each sequence's local structure. Experiments on trained transformers confirm that learned attention patterns match our theoretical construction and approach Bayes-optimal performance, where hard counting fails. Our results bridge mechanistic interpretability of induction heads with classical statistical smoothing, revealing that transformers learn to regularize in-context estimation rather than simply count."},{"id":"60823","en":"Learning to Remember, Learn, and Forget in Attention-Based Models","ko":"Attention 기반 모델에서 기억하고, 학습하고, 잊는 법 배우기","authors":"Djohan Bonnet, Jamie Lohoff, Jan Finkbeiner, Elidona Shiqerukaj, Emre Neftci","pos":"#3014","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=wKMV7mXjUr","abs":"<p>In-Context Learning (ICL) in transformers acts as an online associative memory and is believed to underpin their high performance on complex sequence processing tasks.  However, in gated linear attention models, this memory has a fixed capacity and is prone to interference, especially for long sequences.  We propose Palimpsa, a self-attention model that views ICL as a continual learning problem that must address a stability-plasticity dilemma.  Palimpsa uses Bayesian metaplasticity, where the plasticity of each attention state is tied to an importance state grounded by a prior distribution that captures accumulated knowledge.  We demonstrate that various gated linear attention models emerge as specific architecture choices and posterior approximations, and that Mamba2 is a special case of Palimpsa where forgetting dominates.  This theoretical link enables the transformation of any non-metaplastic model into a metaplastic one, significantly expanding its memory capacity. Our experiments show that Palimpsa consistently outperforms baselines on the Multi-Query Associative Recall (MQAR) benchmark and on Commonsense Reasoning tasks.</p>","absKo":"<p>transformer에서의 In-Context Learning (ICL)은 online associative memory로 작동하며, 복잡한 sequence processing task에서 높은 성능의 기반이라고 여겨진다. 그러나 gated linear attention model에서는 이 memory의 capacity가 고정되어 있고, 특히 긴 sequence에서 interference에 취약하다. 우리는 ICL을 stability-plasticity dilemma를 해결해야 하는 continual learning problem으로 바라보는 self-attention model인 Palimpsa를 제안한다. Palimpsa는 Bayesian metaplasticity를 사용하며, 각 attention state의 plasticity는 축적된 지식을 담는 prior distribution에 의해 구체화된 importance state에 연결된다. 우리는 다양한 gated linear attention model이 특정 architecture choice와 posterior approximation으로부터 도출됨을 보이고, Mamba2는 forgetting이 지배적인 Palimpsa의 특수한 경우임을 보인다. 이 이론적 연결은 어떤 non-metaplastic model도 metaplastic one으로 변환할 수 있게 하여 memory capacity를 크게 확장한다. 우리의 실험은 Palimpsa가 Multi-Query Associative Recall (MQAR) benchmark와 Commonsense Reasoning task에서 baseline을 일관되게 능가함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"63901","en":"MDN: Parallelizing Stepwise Momentum for Delta Linear Attention","ko":"MDN: Delta linear attention을 위한 단계적 momentum 병렬화","authors":"Yulong Huang, Xiang Liu, Hongxiang Huang, Xiaopeng LIN, Zunchang LIU, Xiaowen Chu, Zeke Xie, Bojun Cheng","pos":"#3015","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Sh3rKEAxlW","abs":"<p>Linear Attention (LA) offers a promising paradigm for scaling large language models (LLMs) to long sequences by avoiding the quadratic complexity of self-attention. Recent LA models such as Mamba2 and GDN interpret linear recurrences as closed-form online stochastic gradient descent (SGD), but naive SGD updates suffer from rapid information decay and suboptimal convergence in optimization. While momentum-based optimizers provide a natural remedy, they pose challenges in simultaneously achieving training efficiency and effectiveness. To address this, we develop a chunkwise parallel algorithm for LA with a stepwise momentum rule by geometrically reordering the update coefficients. Further, from a dynamical systems perspective, we analyze the momentum-based recurrence as a second-order system that introduces complex conjugate eigenvalues. This analysis guides the design of stable gating constraints. The resulting model, Momentum DeltaNet (MDN), leverages Triton kernels to achieve comparable training throughput with competitive linear models such as Mamba2 and KDA. Extensive experiments on the 400M and 1.3B parameter models demonstrate consistent performance improvements over strong baselines, including Transformers, Mamba2 and GDN, across diverse downstream evaluation benchmarks.</p>","absKo":"Linear Attention (LA)은 self-attention의 quadratic complexity를 피함으로써 large language models (LLMs)을 긴 sequence로 확장하기 위한 유망한 패러다임을 제공한다. 최근 Mamba2와 GDN 같은 LA 모델은 linear recurrence를 closed-form online stochastic gradient descent (SGD)로 해석하지만, naive SGD update는 빠른 정보 소실과 최적화에서의 비최적 수렴을 보인다. momentum 기반 optimizer는 자연스러운 해결책을 제공하지만, 학습 효율성과 효과를 동시에 달성하는 데 어려움을 준다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 update coefficient를 기하학적으로 재정렬하여 stepwise momentum rule을 갖는 LA용 chunkwise parallel algorithm을 개발한다. 더 나아가 dynamical systems 관점에서 momentum 기반 recurrence를 complex conjugate eigenvalue를 유도하는 second-order system으로 분석한다. 이러한 분석은 안정적인 gating constraint 설계를 이끈다. 그 결과 모델인 Momentum DeltaNet (MDN)은 Triton kernel을 활용해 Mamba2와 KDA 같은 경쟁력 있는 linear model과 비교 가능한 학습 throughput을 달성한다. 400M 및 1.3B parameter 모델에 대한 대규모 실험은 Transformer, Mamba2, GDN을 포함한 강력한 baseline 대비 다양한 downstream evaluation benchmark 전반에서 일관된 성능 향상을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"62207","en":"Neural Attention Search Linear: Towards Adaptive Token-Level Hybrid Attention Models","ko":"Neural Attention Search Linear: 적응형 토큰 수준 하이브리드 어텐션 모델","authors":"Difan Deng, Andreas B. Winje, Lukas Fehring, Marius Lindauer","pos":"#3016","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=igB9562BZJ","abs":"The quadratic computational complexity of softmax transformers has become a bottleneck in long-context scenarios. In contrast, linear attention model families provide a promising direction towards a more efficient sequential model. These linear attention models compress past $KV$ values into a single hidden state, thereby efficiently reducing complexity during both training and inference. However, their expressivity remains limited by the size of their hidden state. Previous work proposed interleaving softmax and linear attention layers to reduce computational complexity while preserving expressivity. Nevertheless, the efficiency of these models remains bottlenecked by their softmax attention layers. In this paper, we propose Neural Attention Search Linear (NAtS-L), a framework that applies both linear attention and softmax attention operations within the same layer on different tokens. NAtS-L automatically determines whether a token can be handled by a linear attention model, i.e., tokens that have only short-term impact and can be encoded into fixed-size hidden states, or require softmax attention, i.e., tokens that contain information related to long-term retrieval and need to be preserved for future queries. By searching for optimal Gated DeltaNet and softmax attention combinations across tokens, we show that NAtS-L provides a strong yet efficient token-level hybrid architecture.","absKo":"softmax transformer의 이차적 계산 복잡도는 긴 context 시나리오에서 병목이 되어 왔다. 반면 linear attention 계열은 더 효율적인 sequential model을 향한 유망한 방향을 제공한다. 이러한 linear attention model은 과거의 $KV$ 값을 단일 hidden state로 압축함으로써, training과 inference 모두에서 복잡도를 효율적으로 줄인다. 그러나 그 표현력은 hidden state의 크기에 의해 여전히 제한된다. 기존 연구는 계산 복잡도를 줄이면서 표현력을 보존하기 위해 softmax attention layer와 linear attention layer를 교차 배치하는 방식을 제안했다. 그럼에도 이들 모델의 효율성은 여전히 softmax attention layer에 의해 병목이 된다. 본 논문에서는 동일한 layer 내에서 서로 다른 token에 대해 linear attention 연산과 softmax attention 연산을 모두 적용하는 프레임워크인 Neural Attention Search Linear(NAtS-L)를 제안한다. NAtS-L은 어떤 token이 linear attention model로 처리 가능할지, 즉 단기적 영향만 가지며 고정 크기 hidden state로 인코딩할 수 있는 token인지, 아니면 softmax attention이 필요한지, 즉 장기적 retrieval과 관련된 정보를 담고 있어 미래의 query를 위해 보존되어야 하는 token인지,를 자동으로 판별한다. token별로 최적의 Gated DeltaNet과 softmax attention 조합을 탐색함으로써, NAtS-L이 강력하면서도 효율적인 token-level hybrid architecture를 제공함을 보인다."},{"id":"63012","en":"AsyncSpade: Efficient Test-Time Scaling with Asynchronous Sparse Decoding","ko":"AsyncSpade: Asynchronous Sparse Decoding으로 효율적인 Test-Time Scaling","authors":"Shixuan Zhang, Yilin Guan, Pingzhi Li, Hanrui Wang, Tianlong Chen","pos":"#3606","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=avVTEzRgba","abs":"Test-time scaling (TTS) can boost LLM reasoning through long chain-of-thought (CoT), but the linear KV-cache growth amplifies the memory-bound bottleneck of LLM decoding. Query-aware sparse decoding methods can achieve state-of-the-art performance under constrained FLOP budget, but are mainly constrained by both sequential-dependent page filtering and coarse-grained token selection, hampering the serving efficiency and model performance on TTS tasks under high concurrency and long CoT scenarios, where token selection can even occupy higher runtime than the forward pipeline itself. In this paper, we first find that the query state of the current decoding token can be approximated in a unified manner from a short sliding window of recent queries, enabling training-free query-aware sparsity without sequential dependency in the decoding loop. Based on the findings, we propose $\\texttt{\\textbf{AsyncSpade}}$, an asynchronous framework for efficient TTS, built on two core components: $\\textbf{(1) a novel light-weight temporal-regressive module}$ that predicts the next-token query state, and $\\textbf{(2) an asynchronous disaggregated framework}$ that decouples the KV cache selection from the auto-regressive decoding loop, overlapping the token-level KV selection with the forward inference computation through asynchronism, thereby eliminating the sequential dependency without sacrificing model performance. We validate the effectiveness of  $\\texttt{AsyncSpade}$ on common LLM serving setups with an A100 node, where $\\texttt{AsyncSpade}$ can fully overlap KV-cache operations with the inference pipeline within a certain workload range, $\\textbf{achieving theoretical optimal time-per-output-token~(TPOT)}$. Specifically,  $\\texttt{AsyncSpade}$ delivers over 20% reduction on TPOT compared to SoTA baseline ($\\textit{i.e.}$ Quest) and at least 50% TPOT reduction compared to full attention on Qwen3-8B and Qwen3-32B models, while matching or surpassing their accuracy on various TTS benchmarks (AIME-24/25, GPQA-Diamond, MATH-500). Our code is available through https://anonymous.4open.science/r/AsyncSpade-063C.","absKo":"Test-time scaling(TTS)은 긴 chain-of-thought(CoT)를 통해 LLM reasoning을 향상시킬 수 있지만, linear KV-cache growth는 LLM decoding의 memory-bound bottleneck을 악화시킨다. Query-aware sparse decoding method는 제한된 FLOP budget 하에서 state-of-the-art performance를 달성할 수 있지만, 주로 sequential-dependent page filtering과 coarse-grained token selection에 제약되어 있으며, 이는 high concurrency와 long CoT scenario에서의 serving efficiency와 model performance를 저해한다. 이러한 상황에서는 token selection이 forward pipeline 자체보다 더 높은 runtime을 차지하기도 한다. 이 논문에서 우리는 먼저 현재 decoding token의 query state가 최근 query의 짧은 sliding window로부터 통일된 방식으로 근사될 수 있음을 발견했으며, 이를 통해 decoding loop에서 sequential dependency 없이 training-free query-aware sparsity를 가능하게 한다. 이러한 발견을 바탕으로 우리는 $\\texttt{\\textbf{AsyncSpade}}$를 제안한다. 이는 효율적인 TTS를 위한 asynchronous framework이며, 두 가지 핵심 구성 요소 위에 구축된다: $\\textbf{(1) next-token query state를 예측하는 새로운 light-weight temporal-regressive module}$ 과 $\\textbf{(2) KV cache selection을 auto-regressive decoding loop로부터 분리하고, asynchronous하게 token-level KV selection과 forward inference computation을 겹치게 하는 asynchronous disaggregated framework}$이다. 이를 통해 model performance를 희생하지 않으면서 sequential dependency를 제거한다. 우리는 A100 node를 사용하는 일반적인 LLM serving setup에서 $\\texttt{AsyncSpade}$의 효과를 검증했으며, $\\texttt{AsyncSpade}$는 특정 workload 범위 내에서 KV-cache operation을 inference pipeline과 완전히 겹칠 수 있어 $\\textbf{theoretical optimal time-per-output-token~(TPOT)}$을 달성한다. 구체적으로, $\\texttt{AsyncSpade}$는 Qwen3-8B 및 Qwen3-32B model에서 SoTA baseline($\\textit{i.e.}$ Quest) 대비 TPOT을 20% 이상 줄이고, full attention 대비 최소 50%의 TPOT 감소를 달성하는 동시에, 다양한 TTS benchmark(AIME-24/25, GPQA-Diamond, MATH-500)에서 정확도를 맞추거나 상회한다. 코드는 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/AsyncSpade-063C 에서 제공된다."},{"id":"65298","en":"PRISM: Sequence Modeling as Parallel Residual Iteration","ko":"PRISM: 병렬 잔차 반복으로서의 시퀀스 모델링","authors":"Jie Jiang, Ke Cheng, Xin Xu, Mengyang Pang, Xinzhe Xu, Jiaheng Li, Yue Liu, Yuan Wang, Jun Zhang, Huan Yu, Zhouchen Lin","pos":"#4009","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Eyz8oboVDt","abs":"Generative sequence modeling faces a fundamental tension between the expressivity of Transformers and the efficiency of linear sequence models. Existing efficient architectures are theoretically bounded by shallow, single-step linear updates, while powerful iterative methods like Test-Time Training (TTT) break hardware parallelism due to state-dependent gradients. We propose PRISM (Parallel Residual Iterative Sequence Model) to resolve this tension. PRISM introduces a solver-inspired inductive bias that captures key structural properties of multi-step refinement in a parallelizable form. We employ a Write-Forget Decoupling strategy that isolates non-linearity within the injection operator. To bypass the serial dependency of explicit solvers, PRISM utilizes a two-stage proxy architecture: a short-convolution anchors the initial residual using local history energy, while a learned predictor estimates the refinement updates directly from the input. This design distills structural patterns associated with iterative correction into a parallelizable feedforward operator. Theoretically, we prove that this formulation achieves Rank-$L$ accumulation, structurally expanding the update manifold beyond the single-step Rank-$1$ bottleneck. Empirically, it achieves comparable performance to explicit optimization methods while achieving \\textbf{174x higher throughput}. Codes are available in \\href{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/msir-F607/}{anonymous.4open.science}."},{"id":"65037","en":"ATLAS: Learning to Optimally Memorize the Context at Test Time","ko":"ATLAS: Test Time에 Context를 최적으로 기억하는 방법 학습","authors":"Ali Behrouz, Zeman Li, Praneeth Kacham, Majid Daliri, Yuan Deng, Peilin Zhong, Meisam Razaviyayn, Vahab Mirrokni","pos":"#4010","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=HV1R5bMSpa","abs":"<p>Transformers have been established as the most popular backbones in sequence modeling, mainly due to their effectiveness in in-context retrieval tasks and the ability to learn at scale. Their quadratic memory and time complexity, however, bound their applicability in longer sequences and so has motivated researchers to explore effective alternative architectures such as modern recurrent neural networks (a.k.a long-term recurrent memory module). Despite their recent success in diverse downstream tasks, they struggle in tasks that requires long context understanding and extrapolation to longer sequences. We observe that these shortcomings come from three disjoint aspects in their design: (1) limited memory capacity that is bounded by the architecture of memory and feature mapping of the input; (2) online nature of update, i.e., optimizing the memory only with respect to the last input; and (3) less expressive management of their fixed-size memory. To enhance all these three aspects, we present Atlas, a long-term memory module with high capacity that learns to memorize the context by optimizing the memory based on the current and past tokens, overcoming the online nature of long-term memory models. Our experimental results on language modeling, common-sense reasoning, recall-intensive, and long-context understanding tasks support the effectiveness of Atlas compared to other modern recurrent neural networks.</p>"},{"id":"64989","en":"Decoupling The \"What\" and \"Where\" With Polar Coordinate Positional Embedding","ko":"극좌표 Positional Embedding으로 '무엇'과 '어디'를 분리하기","authors":"Anand Gopalakrishnan, Róbert Csordás, Jürgen Schmidhuber, Michael Mozer","pos":"#4012","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=I3Z9za1EkO","abs":"<p>The attention mechanism in a Transformer architecture matches key to query based on both content—the what—and position in a sequence—the where. We present an analysis indicating that what and where are entangled in the popular rotary position embedding (RoPE). This entanglement can impair performance particularly when decisions require independent matches on these two factors. We propose an improvement to RoPE, which we call Polar Coordinate Position Embedding or PoPE, that eliminates the what-where confound. PoPE is far superior on a diagnostic task requiring indexing solely by position or by content. On autoregressive sequence modeling in music, genomic, and natural language domains, Transformers using PoPE as the positional encoding scheme outperform baselines using RoPE with respect to evaluation loss (perplexity) and downstream task performance. On language modeling, these gains persist across model scale, from 124M to 774M parameters. Crucially, PoPE shows strong zero-shot length extrapolation capabilities compared not only to RoPE but even a method designed for extrapolation, YaRN, which requires additional fine tuning and frequency interpolation.</p>"},{"id":"66656","en":"Semantic Integrity Matters: Benchmarking and Preserving High-Density Reasoning in KV Cache Compression","ko":"의미 무결성이 중요하다: KV Cache 압축에서 고밀도 추론 벤치마킹 및 보존","authors":"Xiang Liu, Zhenheng Tang, Hong Chen, Peijie Dong, Zeyu Li, Xiuze Zhou, Bo Li, Xuming Hu, Xiaowen Chu","pos":"#4307","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=1fGD4sKs8j","abs":"<p>While Key-Value (KV) cache compression is essential for efficient LLM inference, current evaluations disproportionately focus on \\textbf{sparse retrieval} tasks, potentially masking the degradation of High-Density Reasoning where Chain-of-Thought (CoT) coherence is critical. We introduce KVFundaBench to systematically evaluate this gap, revealing a sharp dichotomy: while retrieval tasks remain robust, reasoning tasks exhibit severe Task-Dependent Degradation under aggressive compression due to disrupted CoT links. Extending our analysis to the DeepSeek-R1 model, we uncover that its specialized attention patterns offer unique insights into the fragility of reasoning chains. Guided by these findings—specifically the necessity of preserving few-shot examples as indivisible \\textbf{Semantic Units}—we propose ShotKV. This approach explicitly separates prefill and decoding phases to prioritize semantic integrity. Empirical results demonstrate that ShotKV achieves 9\\%-18\\% accuracy improvements on long-context generation tasks and effectively generalizes to document QA, all while delivering an 11\\% latency reduction compared to full cache inference.</p>"},{"id":"61173","en":"Alethia: a Foundational Encoder for Voice Deepfakes","ko":"Alethia: 음성 딥페이크를 위한 기반 Encoder","authors":"Yi Zhu, Brahmi Dwivedi, Jayaram Raghuram, Surya Koppisetti","pos":"#2807","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=t2h7QkTnzD","abs":"<p>Existing voice deepfake detection and localization models rely heavily on representations extracted from speech foundation models (SFMs). However, downstream finetuning has now reached a state of diminishing returns. In this paper, we shift the focus to pretraining and propose a novel recipe that combines <em>bottleneck masked embedding prediction with flow-matching based spectrogram reconstruction</em>. The outcome, <em>Alethia</em>, is the first foundational audio encoder for various voice deepfake detection and localization tasks. We evaluate on 5 different tasks with 56 benchmark datasets, and note <em>Alethia</em> significantly outperforms state-of-the-art SFMs with superior robustness to real-world perturbations and zero-shot generalization to unseen domains (e.g., singing deepfakes). We also demonstrate the limitation of discrete targets in masked token prediction, and show the importance of <em>continuous embedding</em> prediction and <em>generative pretraining</em> for capturing deepfake artifacts.</p>","absKo":"<p>기존의 voice deepfake detection 및 localization 모델은 speech foundation model (SFM)에서 추출한 representation에 크게 의존한다. 그러나 downstream finetuning은 이제 수익 체감 상태에 도달했다. 본 논문에서는 초점을 pretraining으로 옮기고, <em>bottleneck masked embedding prediction과 flow-matching 기반 spectrogram reconstruction</em>을 결합한 새로운 레시피를 제안한다. 그 결과물인 <em>Alethia</em>는 다양한 voice deepfake detection 및 localization 태스크를 위한 최초의 foundational audio encoder이다. 우리는 5개의 서로 다른 태스크와 56개의 benchmark dataset에서 평가했으며, <em>Alethia</em>가 실세계 perturbation에 대한 뛰어난 robustness와 보지 못한 domain(예: singing deepfake)에 대한 zero-shot generalization을 바탕으로 state-of-the-art SFM을 크게 능가함을 확인했다. 또한 masked token prediction에서 discrete target의 한계를 보이고, deepfake artifact를 포착하기 위해서는 <em>continuous embedding</em> prediction과 <em>generative pretraining</em>이 중요함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"66416","en":"Curriculum Reinforcement Learning for Black-Box Prompt Tuning via Large Language Models","ko":"대규모 언어 모델을 통한 블랙박스 프롬프트 튜닝을 위한 커리큘럼 강화 학습","authors":"Shuai Gong, Chaoran Cui, Xiaolin Dong, Chunyun Zhang, Linwei Fan","pos":"#1001","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=3vEduRdA9z","abs":"<p>Black-box prompt tuning (BBPT) aims to optimize input prompts for large models where internal parameters and gradients are inaccessible. However, existing methods fail to simultaneously address the dual challenges of prompt interpretability and query efficiency. To address these challenges, we propose CRL-BPT, a curriculum reinforcement learning framework that utilizes a large language model as an agent to generate human-readable prompts. Specifically, CRL-BPT implements a dynamic curriculum schedule on two auxiliary objectives: an imitation loss and an innovation loss. By dynamically weighting these objectives, CRL-BPT regularizes the RL process, guiding the agent from mimicking reference prompts to discovering novel patterns. Additionally, we introduce tailored stabilization mechanisms comprising historical loss normalization and relative reward calibration to ensure robust training. Extensive experiments demonstrate that CRL-BPT establishes new state-of-the-art performance and generates highly interpretable prompts under a strict budget of API calls. Code is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/CRL-BPT.</p>"},{"id":"63970","en":"Synergistic Intra- and Cross-Layer Regularization Losses for MoE Expert Specialization","ko":"MoE 전문가 특화를 위한 층 내부 및 층 간 시너지 정규화 손실","authors":"Rizhen Hu, Yuan Cao, Boao Kong, Mou Sun, Kun Yuan","pos":"#1706","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=S8XPQrBX5y","abs":"Sparse Mixture-of-Experts (MoE) models scale Transformers efficiently but suffer from expert overlap, where different experts process similar tokens and learn redundant functions, resulting in ambiguous routing and underutilized capacity. While architectural solutions like DeepSeek-style shared experts promote specialization, they require substantial structural modifications and rely solely on intra-layer signals. We propose two plug-and-play auxiliary losses that enhance MoE specialization and routing efficiency without modifying routers or model architectures. First, an intra-layer specialization loss penalizes cosine similarity between experts' SwiGLU activations on identical tokens, encouraging experts to specialize in complementary functions. Second, a cross-layer dependency loss maximizes joint Top-$k$  routing probabilities across adjacent layers, establishing coherent expert pathways through network depth while reinforcing intra-layer specialization. Both losses are orthogonal to the standard load-balancing loss and compatible with shared-expert and vanilla Top-$k$  MoE architectures. We implement both losses as a drop-in Megatron-LM module. Extensive experiments across pre-training, fine-tuning, and zero-shot benchmarks demonstrate consistent task gains, higher expert specialization, and lower-entropy routing; together, these improvements translate into faster inference via more stable expert pathways.","absKo":"Sparse Mixture-of-Experts (MoE) 모델은 Transformer를 효율적으로 확장하지만, 서로 다른 expert가 유사한 토큰을 처리하고 중복된 함수를 학습하는 expert overlap 문제를 겪는다. 이로 인해 routing이 모호해지고 capacity가 충분히 활용되지 못한다. DeepSeek 스타일의 shared expert 같은 구조적 해결책은 specialization을 촉진하지만, 상당한 구조적 수정이 필요하고 intra-layer 신호에만 의존한다. 우리는 router나 모델 아키텍처를 수정하지 않고도 MoE specialization과 routing 효율을 향상시키는 두 개의 plug-and-play 보조 loss를 제안한다. 첫째, intra-layer specialization loss는 동일한 토큰에 대한 expert들의 SwiGLU activation 간 cosine similarity를 penalize하여, expert들이 상호 보완적인 기능에 특화되도록 유도한다. 둘째, cross-layer dependency loss는 인접한 layer들에 걸친 joint Top-$k$ routing probability를 최대화하여, intra-layer specialization을 강화하는 동시에 network depth 전반에 걸쳐 일관된 expert pathway를 형성한다. 두 loss는 standard load-balancing loss와 직교적이며 shared-expert 및 vanilla Top-$k$ MoE 아키텍처와 호환된다. 우리는 두 loss를 모두 Megatron-LM의 drop-in module로 구현한다. pre-training, fine-tuning, zero-shot benchmark 전반에 걸친 광범위한 실험은 일관된 task 성능 향상, 더 높은 expert specialization, 더 낮은 entropy routing을 보여 주며, 이러한 개선은 더 안정적인 expert pathway를 통한 더 빠른 inference로 이어진다."},{"id":"60978","en":"Regression Language Models for Code","ko":"Code를 위한 Regression Language Models","authors":"Yash Akhauri, Xingyou Song, Arissa Wongpanich, Bryan Lewandowski, Mohamed Abdelfattah","pos":"#1816","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=utTapVWtc7","abs":"We study \\textbf{code-to-metric regression}: predicting numeric outcomes of code executions, a challenging task due to the open-ended nature of programming languages. While prior methods have resorted to heavy and domain-specific feature engineering, we show that a single unified Regression Language Model (RLM) can simultaneously predict directly from text, (i) the memory footprint of code across multiple high-level languages such as Python and C++, (ii) the latency of Triton GPU kernels, and (iii) the accuracy and speed of trained neural networks represented in ONNX. In particular, a relatively small 300M parameter RLM initialized from T5Gemma, obtains $&gt;$0.9 Spearman-rank on competitive programming submissions from APPS, and a single unified model achieves $&gt;$0.5 average Spearman-rank across 17 separate languages from CodeNet. Furthermore, the RLM can obtain the highest average Kendall-Tau of 0.46 on five classic NAS design spaces previously dominated by graph neural networks, and simultaneously predict architecture latencies on numerous hardware platforms.","absKo":"code-to-metric regression을 연구한다: 즉, programming language의 open-ended한 성격 때문에 어려운 과제인 code execution의 numeric outcome을 예측하는 문제이다. 기존 방법들이 무거운 domain-specific feature engineering에 의존해 온 것과 달리, 우리는 하나의 통합된 Regression Language Model (RLM)이 텍스트로부터 동시에 (i) Python과 C++ 같은 여러 high-level language에 걸친 code의 memory footprint, (ii) Triton GPU kernel의 latency, 그리고 (iii) ONNX로 표현된 trained neural network의 accuracy와 speed를 직접 예측할 수 있음을 보인다. 특히, T5Gemma에서 초기화된 비교적 작은 300M parameter RLM은 APPS의 competitive programming submission에서 $&gt;$0.9 Spearman-rank를 달성하며, 단일 통합 model은 CodeNet의 17개 별도 language 전반에서 평균 $&gt;$0.5 Spearman-rank를 달성한다. 더 나아가 RLM은 이전에는 graph neural network가 지배하던 다섯 개의 classic NAS design space에서 평균 Kendall-Tau 0.46으로 최고 성능을 달성할 수 있으며, 동시에 다양한 hardware platform에서 architecture latency를 예측할 수 있다."},{"id":"60872","en":"When Data Is Scarce: Scaling Sparse Language Models with Repeated Training","ko":"데이터가 부족할 때: 반복 학습으로 Sparse Language Model 확장","authors":"Boqian Wu, Qiao Xiao, Patrik Okanovic, Tomasz Sternal, Maurice Keulen, Mykola Pechenizkiy, Elena Mocanu, Torsten Hoefler, Decebal Constantin Mocanu","pos":"#209","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=vmcs6GBUe4","abs":"<p>Scaling laws for dense LLMs under infinite data are well explored, but how sparsity interacts with limited data is not. In this work, we study sparse training in data-constrained regimes where limited unique tokens require multi-epoch training. Our experiments span models up to 3.84B parameters, sparsity up to 90\\%, and datasets from 1.3B to 41.6B tokens, trained for as many as 16 epochs. We find that: 1. <strong>Sparse scaling in data-limited settings:</strong> We introduce a scaling law that models loss as a function of active parameters, unique tokens, data repetition, and sparsity, accurately predicting performance across compute and data budgets. 2. <strong>Delayed data saturation:</strong> sparse training postpones diminishing returns from repeated data, making multi-epoch training more effective. 3. <strong>Resource trade-offs:</strong> With fixed data, loss-optimal sparsity is moderate (~50%), while compute-optimal sparsity is higher and grows with data scale. Overall, sparsity is not just a tool for efficiency, but a mechanism for improving scaling trade-offs under data scarcity.</p>","absKo":"<p>무한한 데이터 하에서의 dense LLM에 대한 scaling law는 잘 연구되어 있지만, sparsity가 제한된 데이터와 어떻게 상호작용하는지는 충분히 알려져 있지 않다. 이 연구에서는 고유한 토큰 수가 제한되어 multi-epoch training이 필요한 data-constrained regime에서 sparse training을 조사한다. 우리의 실험은 최대 3.84B parameter 모델, 최대 90\\% sparsity, 1.3B에서 41.6B token에 이르는 dataset, 그리고 최대 16 epoch 학습을 포함한다. 우리는 다음을 발견했다: 1. <strong>Data-limited setting에서의 sparse scaling:</strong> active parameter, unique token, data repetition, sparsity의 함수로 loss를 모델링하는 scaling law를 제안하며, compute와 data budget 전반에서 성능을 정확하게 예측한다. 2. <strong>지연된 data saturation:</strong> sparse training은 반복 데이터로 인한 diminishing return을 늦춰 multi-epoch training을 더 효과적으로 만든다. 3. <strong>Resource trade-off:</strong> 데이터가 고정된 경우 loss-optimal sparsity는 중간 수준(~50%)인 반면, compute-optimal sparsity는 더 높고 데이터 규모가 커질수록 증가한다. 전반적으로 sparsity는 단순한 효율화 도구가 아니라, 데이터 희소성 하에서 scaling trade-off를 개선하는 메커니즘이다.</p>"},{"id":"65117","en":"GFMate: Empowering Graph Foundation Models with Pre-training-agnostic Test-time Prompt Tuning","ko":"GFMate: 사전학습 비의존적 Test-time 프롬프트 튜닝으로 Graph Foundation Model 강화하기","authors":"Yan Jiang, Ruihong Qiu, Zi Huang","pos":"#2407","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=GdyuWMAH8P","abs":"<p>Graph prompt tuning has shown great potential in graph learning by introducing trainable prompts to enhance the model performance in conventional single-domain scenarios. Recent research has extended graph prompts to improve Graph Foundation Models (GFMs) by few-shot tuning auxiliary prompts. Despite their progress, most existing methods embed source-domain information into prompts, which serve either as input to GFMs or encoded during model pre-training. Such prompt entanglement with specific source domains and GFM pre-training strategy restricts their generalisability to other domains and different GFMs. Furthermore, existing GFM prompts merely rely on few-shot tuning for adaptation, neglecting the rich information in unlabelled target domain test data. Motivated by these insights, this paper aims to empower GFMs with pre-training-agnostic test-time graph prompt tuning, named GFMate. GFMate introduces centroid and layer prompts applied after pre-training on target domains, avoiding entanglement with specific source domains and model pre-training. In addition, a test-time complementary learning objective is devised to exploit both labelled and unlabelled target domain data for effective test-time prompt tuning. Extensive experiments on 12 benchmark datasets demonstrate the superior performance and efficiency of GFMate, achieving improvements of up to 30.63%. Code will be released upon acceptance.</p>"},{"id":"66511","en":"GraphPFN: A Prior-Data Fitted Network for Graph Node-Level Tasks","ko":"GraphPFN: 그래프 노드 수준 작업을 위한 Prior-Data Fitted Network","authors":"Dmitry Eremeev, Oleg Platonov, Gleb Bazhenov, Artem Babenko, Liudmila Prokhorenkova","pos":"#2411","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=340Ep8sfJ3","abs":"<p>Graph foundation models face several fundamental challenges including transferability across datasets and data scarcity, which calls into question the very feasibility of graph foundation models. However, despite similar challenges, the tabular domain has recently witnessed the emergence of the first successful foundation models such as TabPFNv2 and LimiX. Many of these models are based on the prior-data fitted networks (PFN) framework, in which models are pretrained on carefully designed synthetic datasets to make predictions in an in-context learning setting. Recently, G2T-FM has made the first step towards adopting PFNs for graphs, yet it is limited to hand-crafted features and was never pretrained on graph data. In this work, we make the next step by proposing GraphPFN, a PFN-based model designed and pretrained specifically for graph node-level tasks. Following the PFN framework, we first design a prior distribution of synthetic attributed graphs by using a novel combination of multi-level stochastic block models and a preferential attachment process for structure generation and graph-aware structured causal models for attribute generation. Then, we augment the tabular foundation model LimiX with attention-based graph neighborhood aggregation layers and train it on synthetic graphs sampled from our prior. On diverse real-world graph datasets with node-level tasks, GraphPFN shows strong in-context learning performance and achieves state-of-the-art results after finetuning, outperforming both G2T-FM and task-specific GNNs trained from scratch on most datasets. More broadly, GraphPFN shows the potential of PFN-based models for building graph foundation models.</p>"},{"id":"66494","en":"h1: Bootstrapping LLMs to Reason over Longer Horizons via Reinforcement Learning","ko":"h1: 강화 학습을 통해 더 긴 지평에 걸쳐 추론하도록 LLM 부트스트래핑","authors":"Alesia Ivanova, Sumeet Motwani, Jack Cai, Phil Torr, Riashat Islam, Shital Shah, Christian Schroeder de Witt, Charles London","pos":"#2704","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=3BW15kSPfN","abs":"<p>Large language models excel at short-horizon reasoning tasks, but performance drops as reasoning horizon lengths increase. Existing approaches to combat this rely on inference-time scaffolding or step-level supervision, neither of which scales easily. In this work, we introduce a scalable method to bootstrap long-horizon reasoning capabilities using only existing, abundant short-horizon data. Our approach synthetically composes simple problems into complex, multi-step dependency chains of arbitrary length. We train models on this data using outcome-only rewards under a curriculum that automatically increases in complexity, allowing RL training to be scaled much further without saturating. Empirically, our method generalizes remarkably well: curriculum training on composed 6th-grade level math problems (GSM8K) improves accuracy on longer, competition-level benchmarks (GSM-Symbolic, MATH-500, AIME). It also transfers significantly to diverse out-of-distribution ReasoningGym domains and long-context benchmarks, indicating broader generalization. Importantly, our long-horizon improvements are significantly higher than baselines even at high pass@k, showing that models can learn new reasoning paths under RL. Theoretically, we show that curriculum RL with outcome rewards could achieve an exponential improvement in sample complexity over full-horizon training, providing training signal comparable to dense supervision. h1 therefore introduces an efficient path towards scaling RL for long-horizon problems using only existing data.</p>"},{"id":"66252","en":"UI2Code^N: UI-to-Code Generation as Interactive Visual Optimization","ko":"UI2Code^N: 대화형 시각 최적화로서의 UI-to-Code 생성","authors":"ZHEN YANG, Wenyi Hong, Mingde Xu, Xinyue Fan, Weihan Wang, Jiale Cheng, Xiaotao Gu, Jie Tang","pos":"#2705","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=5Q4hoiHhoU","abs":"UI-to-code aims to translate UI screenshots into executable front-end code. Despite progress with vision-language models (VLMs), most existing methods formulate UI-to-code as a single-pass generation, which mismatches real-world UI development that is inherently iterative and feedback-driven. We reformulate UI-to-code as an interactive visual optimization problem, where code generation is embedded in a closed-loop process of execution, visual inspection, and iterative refinement driven by rendered visual feedback. To address the non-differentiability of visual objectives and the noise of absolute visual evaluators, we propose Relative Visual Policy Optimization (RVPO), a preference-based reinforcement learning method that optimizes relative visual rankings among rendered candidates under execution feedback. We instantiate this paradigm in UI2Code$^{\\text{N}}$, an open-source 9B model trained via continual pre-training, supervised fine-tuning, and reinforcement learning. Experiments demonstrate state-of-the-art performance on UI drafting, UI polishing, and UI editing benchmarks, even outperforming larger models, with performance consistently improving through iterative visual optimization."},{"id":"64358","en":"Toward Effective Multimodal Graph Foundation Model: A Divide-and-Conquer Based Approach","ko":"효과적인 멀티모달 그래프 파운데이션 모델을 향하여: 분할 정복 기반 접근법","authors":"Sicheng Liu, Xunkai Li, Daohan Su, Ru Zhang, Hongchao Qin, Rong-Hua Li, Guoren Wang","pos":"#2707","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=OOodUUenVk","abs":"<p>Graph Foundation Models (GFMs) have achieved remarkable success in generalizing across diverse domains. However, they mainly focus on Text-Attributed Graphs (TAGs), leaving Multimodal-Attributed Graphs (MAGs) largely untapped. Developing Multimodal Graph Foundation Models (MGFMs) allows for leveraging the rich multimodal information in MAGs, and extends applicability to broader types of downstream tasks. While recent MGFMs integrate diverse modality information, our empirical investigation reveals two fundamental limitations of existing MGFMs: (1)they fail to explicitly model modality interaction, essential for capturing intricate cross-modal semantics beyond simple aggregation, and (2)they exhibit sub-optimal modality alignment, which is critical for bridging the significant semantic disparity between distinct modal spaces. To address these challenges, we propose PLANET (graPh topoLogy-aware modAlity iNteraction and alignmEnT), a novel framework employing a Divide-and-Conquer strategy to decouple modality interaction and alignment across distinct granularities. At the embedding granularity, (1)Embedding-wise Domain Gating (EDG) performs local semantic enrichment by adaptively infusing topology-aware cross-modal context, achieving modality interaction. At the node granularity, (2)Node-wise Discretization Retrieval (NDR) ensures global modality alignment by constructing a Discretized Semantic Representation Space (DSRS) to bridge modality gaps. Extensive experiments demonstrate that PLANET significantly outperforms state-of-the-art baselines across diverse graph-centric and multimodal generative tasks.</p>","absKo":"<p>Graph Foundation Model(GFM)은 다양한 도메인 전반에서 일반화에 탁월한 성과를 보여 왔습니다. 그러나 주로 Text-Attributed Graph(TAG)에 초점을 맞추고 있어, Multimodal-Attributed Graph(MAG)는 크게 활용되지 못하고 있습니다. Multimodal Graph Foundation Model(MGFM)을 개발하면 MAG에 내재한 풍부한 multimodal information을 활용할 수 있으며, 더 넓은 종류의 downstream task로의 적용성도 확장됩니다. 최근의 MGFM은 다양한 modality 정보를 통합하지만, 우리의 실증적 조사에 따르면 기존 MGFM에는 두 가지 근본적 한계가 있습니다. (1) 단순한 aggregation을 넘어 복잡한 cross-modal semantics를 포착하는 데 필수적인 modality interaction을 명시적으로 model하지 못하며, (2) 서로 다른 modal space 사이의 큰 semantic disparity를 메우는 데 중요한 modality alignment가 최적이 아닙니다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 서로 다른 granularity 전반에서 modality interaction과 alignment를 분리하는 Divide-and-Conquer 전략을 채택한 새로운 framework인 PLANET(graPh topoLogy-aware modAlity iNteraction and alignmEnT)을 제안합니다. embedding granularity에서는 (1) Embedding-wise Domain Gating(EDG)이 topology-aware cross-modal context를 적응적으로 주입하여 local semantic enrichment를 수행함으로써 modality interaction을 달성합니다. node granularity에서는 (2) Node-wise Discretization Retrieval(NDR)이 Discretized Semantic Representation Space(DSRS)를 구축하여 modality gap을 메움으로써 global modality alignment를 보장합니다. 광범위한 실험은 PLANET이 다양한 graph-centric 및 multimodal generative task 전반에서 state-of-the-art baseline보다 크게 우수함을 보여줍니다.</p>"},{"id":"63874","en":"TabICooL: A better, faster, scalable, and open tabular foundation model","ko":"TabICooL: 더 좋고, 더 빠르고, 더 확장 가능하며, 오픈된 tabular foundation model","authors":"Jingang QU, David Holzmüller, Gael Varoquaux, Marine Le Morvan","pos":"#2708","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=SxsyLjIfWB","abs":"<p>Tabular foundation models, such as TabPFNv2 and TabICL, have recently dethroned gradient-boosted trees at the top of predictive benchmarks, demonstrating the value of in-context learning for tabular data. We introduce TabICooL, a new state-of-the-art foundation model for regression and classification built on three pillars: (1) a novel synthetic data generation engine designed for high pretraining diversity; (2) various architectural innovations, including a new scalable softmax in attention improving generalization to larger datasets without prohibitive long-sequence pretraining; and (3) optimized pretraining protocols, notably replacing AdamW with the Muon optimizer. On the TabArena and TALENT benchmarks, TabICooL without any tuning matches or surpasses the performance of the current state-of-the-art, RealTabPFN-2.5 (hyperparameter-tuned, ensembled, and fine-tuned on real data). With only moderate pretraining compute, TabICooL generalizes effectively to million-scale datasets under 50GB GPU memory while being markedly faster than RealTabPFN-2.5. We provide extensive ablation studies to quantify these contributions and commit to open research by releasing our weights, synthetic data engine, and pretraining code (upon publication).</p>","absKo":"<p>TabPFNv2와 TabICL 같은 tabular foundation model은 최근 predictive benchmark에서 gradient-boosted tree를 제치고 선두에 올라, tabular data에 대한 in-context learning의 가치를 입증했다. 우리는 세 가지 기둥 위에 구축된 regression 및 classification용 새로운 state-of-the-art foundation model인 TabICooL을 소개한다: (1) 높은 pretraining diversity를 위해 설계된 새로운 synthetic data generation engine; (2) 주목(attention)에서 새로운 scalable softmax를 포함한 다양한 architectural innovation으로, 장시간 sequence pretraining의 과도한 비용 없이 더 큰 dataset에 대한 generalization을 향상; (3) 최적화된 pretraining protocol, 특히 AdamW를 Muon optimizer로 대체한 점. TabArena와 TALENT benchmark에서, 어떤 tuning도 하지 않은 TabICooL은 현재 state-of-the-art인 RealTabPFN-2.5(하이퍼파라미터 tuning, ensemble, 그리고 real data로 fine-tuning됨)와 동등하거나 이를 능가한다. 적당한 수준의 pretraining compute만으로도, TabICooL은 50GB GPU memory 미만에서 million-scale dataset으로 효과적으로 generalize하면서 RealTabPFN-2.5보다 현저히 빠르다. 우리는 이러한 기여를 정량화하기 위한 광범위한 ablation study를 제공하고, 가중치, synthetic data engine, pretraining code를 공개함으로써(open publication 시) 개방형 연구에 기여할 것을 약속한다.</p>"},{"id":"62011","en":"Relational In-Context Learning via Synthetic Pre-training with Structural Prior","ko":"구조적 prior를 갖는 synthetic pre-training 기반 relational in-context learning","authors":"Yanbo Wang, Jiaxuan You, Chuan Shi, Muhan Zhang","pos":"#2711","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=kiSm94YKor","abs":"<p>Relational Databases (RDBs) are the backbone of modern business, yet they have missed the Foundation Model revolution. Unlike text or images, high-quality RDB data is private and scarce, rendering the standard approach of ``pre-training on the internet'' infeasible. Consequently, existing solutions typically rely on limited real-world datasets, requiring costly fine-tuning to achieve viable performance. To overcome this data scarcity, we introduce RDB-PFN, the first foundation model for databases trained purely on synthetic data. Drawing inspiration from Prior-Data Fitted Networks (PFNs) where synthetic data generated from Structural Causal Models (SCMs) enables reasoning on i.i.d. single tables, we construct a novel Relational Prior Generator to create an infinite stream of random, complex, and diverse database schemas from scratch. By pre-training on a large-scale curriculum of over 2 million synthetic single-table and relational tasks, RDB-PFN learns to adapt to any new database instantly via genuine In-Context Learning. Experiments demonstrate that RDB-PFN outperforms both fine-tuned Graph Foundation Models and state-of-the-art Single-Table Foundation Models on real-world benchmarks. Notably, these results are achieved using a naive model architecture, proving that a rigorously defined synthetic generator is all you need to solve relational reasoning.</p>","absKo":"<p>Relational Databases(RDBs)는 현대 비즈니스의 핵심이지만, Foundation Model 혁명에서는 소외되어 왔다. 텍스트나 이미지와 달리 고품질 RDB 데이터는 private하고 희소하여, 표준적인 ``인터넷에서 pre-training'' 접근은 비현실적이다. 그 결과, 기존 솔루션은 대개 제한된 실제 데이터셋에 의존하며, 실용적 성능을 얻기 위해 비용이 큰 fine-tuning을 요구한다. 이러한 데이터 부족 문제를 극복하기 위해, 우리는 synthetic data만으로 학습된 데이터베이스용 최초의 foundation model인 RDB-PFN을 소개한다. Structural Causal Model(SCM)에서 생성된 synthetic data를 통해 i.i.d. single-table에서 추론을 가능하게 하는 Prior-Data Fitted Network(PFN)에 착안하여, 우리는 처음부터 무한한 random, complex, diverse database schema 스트림을 생성하는 새로운 Relational Prior Generator를 구성한다. 200만 개가 넘는 synthetic single-table 및 relational task로 구성된 대규모 curriculum으로 pre-training함으로써, RDB-PFN은 진정한 In-Context Learning을 통해 어떤 새로운 database에도 즉시 적응하는 법을 학습한다. 실험 결과, RDB-PFN은 실제 benchmark에서 fine-tuned Graph Foundation Model과 최신 Single-Table Foundation Model을 모두 능가한다. 특히, 이러한 결과는 소박한 model architecture를 사용해 달성되었으며, 엄밀하게 정의된 synthetic generator만으로 relational reasoning을 해결할 수 있음을 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"61320","en":"PluRel: Synthetic Data unlocks Scaling Laws for Relational Foundation Models","ko":"PluRel: 합성 데이터가 관계형 Foundation Model의 Scaling Law를 열다","authors":"Vignesh Kothapalli, Rishabh Ranjan, Valter Hudovernik, Vijay Prakash Dwivedi, Johannes Hoffart, Carlos Guestrin, Jure Leskovec","pos":"#2715","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=rM9r9qyRSA","abs":"<p>Relational Foundation Models (RFMs) facilitate data-driven decision-making by learning from complex multi-table databases. However, the diverse relational databases needed to train such models are rarely public due to privacy constraints. While there are methods to generate synthetic tabular data of arbitrary size, incorporating schema structure and primary--foreign key connectivity for multi-table generation remains challenging. Here we introduce PluRel, a framework to synthesize multi-tabular relational databases from scratch. In a step-by-step fashion, PluRel models (1) schemas with directed graphs, (2) inter-table primary-foreign key connectivity with bipartite graphs, and, (3) feature distributions in tables via conditional causal mechanisms. The design space across these stages supports the synthesis of a wide range of diverse databases, while being computationally lightweight. Using PluRel, we observe for the first time that (1) RFM pretraining loss exhibits power-law scaling with the number of synthetic databases and total pretraining tokens, (2) scaling the number of synthetic databases improves generalization to real databases, and (3) synthetic pretraining yields strong base models for continued pretraining on real databases. Overall, our framework and results position synthetic data scaling as a promising paradigm for RFMs.</p>","absKo":"<p>Relational Foundation Models(RFMs)는 복잡한 multi-table database로부터 학습하여 data-driven decision-making을 가능하게 한다. 그러나 이러한 model을 학습하는 데 필요한 다양한 relational database는 privacy 제약 때문에 공개되어 있는 경우가 드물다. 임의의 크기의 synthetic tabular data를 생성하는 방법들은 존재하지만, multi-table 생성을 위해 schema structure와 primary--foreign key connectivity를 통합하는 것은 여전히 어렵다. 여기서는 multi-tabular relational database를 처음부터 합성하는 framework인 PluRel을 소개한다. PluRel은 단계적으로 (1) directed graph로 schema를 모델링하고, (2) bipartite graph로 테이블 간 primary-foreign key 연결을 모델링하며, (3) conditional causal mechanism을 통해 테이블 내 feature distribution을 모델링한다. 이러한 단계들에 걸친 design space는 계산적으로 가벼우면서도 매우 다양한 database의 합성을 지원한다. PluRel을 사용하여 우리는 처음으로 (1) RFM pretraining loss가 synthetic database 수와 총 pretraining token 수에 대해 power-law scaling을 보인다는 점, (2) synthetic database 수를 늘리면 실제 database로의 generalization이 향상된다는 점, (3) synthetic pretraining이 실제 database에서 continued pretraining을 위한 강력한 base model을 제공한다는 점을 관찰한다. 전반적으로, 우리 framework와 결과는 synthetic data scaling을 RFMs를 위한 유망한 패러다임으로 자리매김한다.</p>"},{"id":"62299","en":"No Need to Train Your RDB Foundation Model","ko":"RDB Foundation Model을 따로 학습할 필요가 없음","authors":"Minjie Wang, Quan Gan, Linjie Xu, David Wipf, Yanlin Zhang","pos":"#2716","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=hrtEiSftwk","abs":"<p>Relational databases (RDBs) contain vast amounts of heterogeneous tabular information that can be exploited for predictive modeling purposes.  But since the space of potential targets is vast across enterprise settings, how can we avoid retraining a new model each time we wish to predict a new quantity of interest?  Foundation models based on in-context learning (ICL) offer a convenient option, but so far are largely restricted to single-table operability.  In generalizing to multiple interrelated tables, it is essential to compress variably-sized RDB neighborhoods into fixed-length ICL samples for consumption by the decoder.  However, the details here are critical: unlike existing supervised learning RDB pipelines, we provide theoretical and empirical evidence that ICL-specific compression should be constrained within high-dimensional RDB columns where all entities share units and roles, not across columns where the relevance of heterogeneous data types cannot possibly be determined without label information.  Conditioned on this restriction, we then demonstrate that encoder expressiveness is actually not compromised by excluding trainable parameters.  Hence we arrive at a principled family of RDB encoders that can be seamlessly paired with the most powerful single-table ICL foundation models.  From a practical standpoint, we develop scalable SQL primitives to implement the encoder stage, resulting in an easy-to-use open-source RDB foundation model capable of robust performance on completely new datasets out of the box, with no training or fine-tuning required.</p>","absKo":"<p>Relational databases (RDBs)는 predictive modeling에 활용할 수 있는 방대한 heterogeneous tabular information을 담고 있다. 하지만 enterprise 환경 전반에서 잠재적 target의 공간이 매우 넓기 때문에, 관심 있는 새로운 quantity를 예측할 때마다 새로운 model을 다시 학습하는 일을 어떻게 피할 수 있을까? in-context learning (ICL)에 기반한 foundation models는 편리한 선택지를 제공하지만, 지금까지는 주로 single-table operability에 국한되어 왔다. 상호 연관된 여러 table로 일반화하려면, decoder가 소비할 수 있도록 크기가 가변적인 RDB neighborhood를 fixed-length ICL samples로 압축하는 것이 필수적이다. 그러나 세부 사항이 중요하다. 기존 supervised learning RDB pipelines와 달리, 우리는 이론적 및 실험적 근거를 통해 ICL-specific compression은 모든 entity가 같은 units와 roles를 공유하는 고차원 RDB columns 내부에서만 제한되어야 하며, label information 없이는 heterogeneous data types의 relevance를 판별할 수 없는 columns 사이에서는 이루어져서는 안 된다고 보인다. 이 제약을 조건으로 하면, trainable parameters를 제외해도 encoder expressiveness가 실제로 저하되지 않음을 보일 수 있다. 따라서 우리는 가장 강력한 single-table ICL foundation models와 매끄럽게 결합될 수 있는 원칙적인 RDB encoders 계열에 도달한다. 실용적인 관점에서, 우리는 encoder 단계를 구현하기 위한 scalable SQL primitives를 개발하여, 학습이나 fine-tuning 없이도 완전히 새로운 datasets에서 즉시 robust performance를 내는 사용하기 쉬운 open-source RDB foundation model을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"60598","en":"ConceptMoE: Adaptive Token-to-Concept Compression for Implicit Compute Allocation","ko":"ConceptMoE: 암시적 계산 할당을 위한 적응형 토큰-개념 압축","authors":"Zihao Huang, Jundong Zhou, Xingwei Qu, Qiyang Min, Ge Zhang","pos":"#2809","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=yaUJPj48wa","abs":"Large language models allocate uniform computation across all tokens, ignoring that some sequences are trivially predictable while others require deep reasoning. We introduce ConceptMoE, which dynamically merges semantically similar tokens into concepts through learnable chunking at target compression ratio $R$. The MoE architecture enables controlled evaluation: reallocating saved computation to match baseline FLOPs and parameters isolates genuine architectural benefits. ConceptMoE consistently outperforms standard MoE, achieving +0.9 points on language pretraining, +2.3 on long context, and +0.6 on multimodal tasks. Continual training conversion with layer looping gains +5.5 points. Beyond performance, at $R=2$, ConceptMoE reduces attention computation by $R^2\\times$ and KV cache by $R\\times$, delivering prefill speedups up to 175\\% and decoding speedups up to 117\\%. The minimal architectural changes enable straightforward integration, demonstrating that adaptive concept-level processing fundamentally improves LLM effectiveness and efficiency.","absKo":"대규모 언어 모델은 모든 token에 동일한 연산을 할당하여, 어떤 sequence는 매우 쉽게 예측 가능한 반면 다른 sequence는 깊은 추론을 요구한다는 점을 무시한다. 우리는 ConceptMoE를 제안하는데, 이는 목표 압축 비율 $R$에서 학습 가능한 chunking을 통해 의미적으로 유사한 token들을 동적으로 concept으로 병합한다. MoE architecture는 제어된 평가를 가능하게 한다: 절약된 연산을 baseline FLOPs와 parameter에 맞게 재할당함으로써 진정한 architectural benefit을 분리해낸다. ConceptMoE는 표준 MoE를 일관되게 능가하며, language pretraining에서 +0.9점, long context에서 +2.3점, multimodal task에서 +0.6점을 달성한다. layer looping을 사용하는 continual training conversion은 +5.5점을 더한다. 성능을 넘어, $R=2$에서 ConceptMoE는 attention computation을 $R^2\\times$ 줄이고 KV cache를 $R\\times$ 줄여, prefill speedup 최대 175\\%, decoding speedup 최대 117\\%를 제공한다. 최소한의 architectural change만으로도 손쉬운 통합이 가능하며, adaptive concept-level processing이 LLM의 효과성과 효율성을 근본적으로 향상시킴을 보여준다."},{"id":"62368","en":"DTop-p MoE: Sparsity-Controlled Dynamic Top-p MoE for Foundation Model Pre-training","ko":"DTop-p MoE: 파운데이션 모델 사전학습을 위한 Sparsity-Controlled Dynamic Top-p MoE","authors":"Can Jin, Hongwu Peng, Mingcan Xiang, Qixin Zhang, Xiangchi Yuan, Amit Hasan, Ohi Dibua, Yifan Gong, Yan Kang, Dimitris Metaxas","pos":"#2810","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=hEvt3HWxD3","abs":"Sparse Mixture-of-Experts architectures are essential for scaling model capacity efficiently, yet the standard Top-$k$ routing imposes a rigid sparsity pattern that ignores the intrinsic variance in token difficulty and layer-specific computational needs. While Top-$p$ routing offers a flexible alternative, we demonstrate that existing naive Top-$p$ implementations with fixed global probability thresholds provide only marginal gains over Top-$k$, suffer from hyperparameter sensitivity, and result in uncontrolled computational costs. In this paper, we propose $\\texttt{DTop-}p$, a sparsity-controllable dynamic routing mechanism. To overcome the non-differentiability of the MoE sparsity level - the Top-$p$ threshold, we utilize a Proportional-Integral controller that dynamically learns the Top-$p$ probability threshold to align the running sparsity with a user-defined budget. Furthermore, we introduce dynamic routing normalization to adaptively rescale logits, enabling distinct expert selection patterns across layers under a global sparsity constraint. Extensive experiments on Large Language Models and Diffusion Transformers demonstrate that $\\texttt{DTop-}p$ consistently outperforms both Top-$k$ and fixed Top-$p$ baselines while matching the average FLOPs of Top-$k$ MoE. Our analysis confirms that $\\texttt{DTop-}p$ exhibits strong scaling properties across expert granularity, total expert capacity, model size, and dataset size, offering a robust and efficient MoE framework for foundation model pre-training.","absKo":"Sparse Mixture-of-Experts 아키텍처는 model capacity를 효율적으로 확장하는 데 필수적이지만, 표준 Top-$k$ routing은 token 난이도의 본질적 분산과 layer별 계산 요구를 무시하는 경직된 sparsity pattern을 강제한다. Top-$p$ routing은 더 유연한 대안이지만, 우리는 고정된 global probability threshold를 사용하는 기존의 naive Top-$p$ 구현이 Top-$k$ 대비 이득이 미미하고, hyperparameter 민감성이 크며, 계산 비용이 통제되지 않는다는 점을 보인다. 이 논문에서는 sparsity를 제어할 수 있는 dynamic routing 메커니즘인 $\\texttt{DTop-}p$를 제안한다. MoE sparsity level, 즉 Top-$p$ threshold의 비미분성 문제를 극복하기 위해, 우리는 Proportional-Integral controller를 사용하여 user-defined budget에 맞추도록 running sparsity와 정렬되게 Top-$p$ probability threshold를 동적으로 학습한다. 또한 dynamic routing normalization을 도입하여 logits를 적응적으로 재스케일링함으로써, global sparsity constraint 하에서 layer마다 서로 다른 expert selection pattern을 가능하게 한다. Large Language Models와 Diffusion Transformers에 대한 광범위한 실험은 $\\texttt{DTop-}p$가 Top-$k$ 및 fixed Top-$p$ baseline 모두를 일관되게 능가하면서도 Top-$k$ MoE의 평균 FLOPs와는 맞먹는 성능을 보임을 입증한다. 우리의 분석은 $\\texttt{DTop-}p$가 expert granularity, total expert capacity, model size, dataset size 전반에 걸쳐 강한 scaling property를 보이며, foundation model pre-training을 위한 강건하고 효율적인 MoE framework를 제공함을 확인한다."},{"id":"65994","en":"End-to-End Compression for Tabular Foundation Models","ko":"테이블형 기반 모델을 위한 종단간 압축","authors":"Guri Zabërgja, Rafiq Kamel, Arlind Kadra, Christian Frey, Josif Grabocka","pos":"#2811","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=84mfkGDxYh","abs":"<p>The long-standing dominance of gradient-boosted decision trees for tabular data has recently been challenged by in-context learning tabular foundation models. In-context learning methods fit and predict in one forward pass without parameter updates by leveraging the training data as context for predicting on query test points.  While recent tabular foundation models achieve state-of-the-art performance, their transformer architecture based on the attention mechanism has quadratic complexity regarding dataset size, which in turn increases the overhead on training and inference time, and limits the capacity of the models to handle large-scale datasets. In this work, we propose TACO, an end-to-end tabular compression model that compresses the training dataset in a latent space. We test our method on the TabArena benchmark, where our proposed method is up to 94x faster in inference time, while consuming up to 97% less memory compared to the state-of-the-art tabular Transformer architecture, all while retaining performance without significant degradation. Lastly, our method not only scales better with increased dataset sizes, but it also achieves better performance compared to other baselines.</p>"},{"id":"60786","en":"From Zero to Hero: Advancing Zero-Shot Foundation Models for Tabular Outlier Detection","ko":"From Zero to Hero: Tabular Outlier Detection을 위한 Zero-Shot Foundation Model 발전","authors":"Xueying Ding, Haomin Wen, Simon Klüttermann, Leman Akoglu","pos":"#2812","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=wjpdXrHxUi","abs":"<p>Outlier detection (OD) is widely used in practice; but its effective deployment on new tasks is hindered by lack of labeled outliers, which makes algorithm and hyperparameter selection notoriously hard. Foundation models (FMs) have transformed ML, and OD is no exception: Shen et al. (2025) introduced FOMO-0D, the first FM for OD, achieving remarkable performance against numerous baselines. This work introduces OUTFORMER, which advances FOMO-0D with (1) a mixture of synthetic priors and (2) self-evolving curriculum training. OUTFORMER is pretrained solely on synthetic labeled datasets and infers test labels of a new task by using its training data as in-context input. Inference is fast and zero-shot, requiring merely forward pass and no labeled outliers. Thanks to in-context learning, it requires zero additional work—no OD model training or bespoke model selection—enabling truly plug-and-play deployment. OUTFORMER achieves state-of-the-art performance on the prominent ADBench, as well as two new large-scale OD benchmarks that we introduce, comprising over 1,500 datasets, while maintaining speedy inference.</p>","absKo":"<p>Outlier detection(OD)은 실무에서 널리 사용되지만, 새로운 task에 효과적으로 배치하는 데는 labeled outlier의 부족이 큰 장애가 된다. 이는 algorithm과 hyperparameter selection을 매우 어렵게 만든다. Foundation model(FM)은 ML을 변화시켰고, OD도 예외가 아니다. Shen et al. (2025)은 OD를 위한 최초의 FM인 FOMO-0D를 소개하며, 수많은 baseline에 비해 놀라운 성능을 달성했다. 본 연구는 (1) synthetic prior의 mixture와 (2) self-evolving curriculum training을 통해 FOMO-0D를 확장하는 OUTFORMER를 제안한다. OUTFORMER는 synthetic labeled dataset에만 사전 학습되며, training data를 in-context input으로 사용하여 새로운 task의 test label을 추론한다. 추론은 빠르고 zero-shot이며, 단지 forward pass만 필요하고 labeled outlier는 전혀 필요하지 않다. in-context learning 덕분에 추가 작업이 전혀 들지 않아, OD model training이나 맞춤형 model selection이 필요 없으며, 진정한 plug-and-play deployment를 가능하게 한다. OUTFORMER는 우리가 새로 도입하는 두 개의 대규모 OD benchmark를 포함해, 1,500개가 넘는 dataset으로 구성된 대표적인 ADBench에서 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성하면서도 빠른 추론 속도를 유지한다.</p>"},{"id":"66111","en":"Graph is a Substrate Across Data Modalities","ko":"그래프는 데이터 모달리티를 아우르는 기반이다","authors":"Ziming Li, Xiao-Ming Wu, Zehong Wang, Jiazheng Li, Yijun Tian, Jinhe Bi, Yunpu Ma, Yanfang Ye, Chuxu Zhang","pos":"#2813","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=6xKzkSqyef","abs":"<p>Graphs provide a natural representation of relational structure that arises across diverse domains.  Despite this ubiquity, graph structure is typically learned in a modality- and task-isolated manner, where graph representations are constructed within individual task contexts and discarded thereafter.  As a result, structural regularities across modalities and tasks are repeatedly reconstructed rather than accumulated at the level of intermediate graph representations.  This motivates a representation-learning question: <em>how should graph structure be organized so that it can persist and accumulate across heterogeneous modalities and tasks?</em> We adopt a representation-centric perspective in which graph structure is treated as a structural substrate that persists across learning contexts. To instantiate this perspective, we propose <strong>G-Substrate</strong>, a <strong>g</strong>raph <strong>substrate</strong> framework that organizes learning around shared graph structures. G-Substrate comprises two complementary mechanisms: a unified structural schema that ensures compatibility among graph representations across heterogeneous modalities and tasks, and an interleaved role-based training strategy that exposes the same graph structure to multiple functional roles during learning.  Experiments across multiple domains, modalities, and tasks show that G-Substrate outperforms task-isolated and naive multi-task learning methods.</p>"},{"id":"64871","en":"Is One Layer Enough? Understanding Inference Dynamics in Tabular Foundation Models","ko":"한 계층으로 충분한가? Tabular Foundation Model의 추론 동역학 이해","authors":"Amir Rezaei Balef, Mykhailo Koshil, Katharina Eggensperger","pos":"#2814","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=IxpVGcg39J","abs":"<p>Transformer-based tabular foundation models (TFMs) dominate small to medium tabular predictive benchmark tasks, yet their inference mechanisms remain largely unexplored. We present the first large-scale mechanistic study of layerwise dynamics in 6 state-of-the-art tabular in-context learning models. We explore how predictions emerge across depth, identify distinct stages of inference and reveal latent-space dynamics that differ from those of language models. Our findings indicate substantial depthwise redundancy across multiple models, suggesting iterative refinement with overlapping computations during inference stages. Guided by these insights, we design a proof-of-concept, looped single-layer model that uses only 20% of the original model’s parameters while achieving comparable performance.</p>"},{"id":"60757","en":"NanoFLUX: Distillation-Driven Compression of Large Text-to-Image Generation Models for Mobile Devices","ko":"NanoFLUX: 모바일 기기를 위한 대형 Text-to-Image 생성 모델의 Distillation 기반 압축","authors":"Ruchika Chavhan, Malcolm Chadwick, Alberto Gil Couto Pimentel Ramos, Luca Morreale, Mehdi Noroozi, Abhinav Mehrotra","pos":"#2816","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=wvQjM6G4Hh","abs":"While large-scale text-to-image diffusion models continue to improve in visual quality, their increasing scale has widened the gap between state-of-the-art models and on-device solutions. To address this gap, we introduce NanoFLUX, a **2.4B** text-to-image flow-matching model distilled from **17B** FLUX.1-Schnell using a progressive compression pipeline designed to preserve generation quality. Our contributions include: (1) A model compression strategy driven by pruning redundant components in the diffusion transformer, reducing its size from 12B to 2B; (2) A ResNet-based token downsampling mechanism that reduces latency by allowing intermediate blocks to operate on lower-resolution tokens while preserving high-resolution processing elsewhere; (3) A novel text encoder distillation approach that leverages visual signals from early layers of the denoiser during sampling. Empirically, NanoFLUX generates $512 \\times 512$ images in approximately 2.5 seconds on mobile devices, demonstrating the feasibility of high-quality on-device text-to-image generation.","absKo":"대규모 text-to-image diffusion model은 시각적 품질에서 계속 향상되고 있지만, 규모가 커질수록 최첨단 모델과 on-device solution 사이의 격차는 더 넓어지고 있다. 이 격차를 해소하기 위해, 우리는 생성 품질을 보존하도록 설계된 progressive compression pipeline을 사용해 **17B** FLUX.1-Schnell에서 distill한 **2.4B** text-to-image flow-matching model인 NanoFLUX를 소개한다. 우리의 기여는 다음과 같다: (1) diffusion transformer의 redundant component를 pruning하는 model compression strategy를 통해 크기를 12B에서 2B로 줄였다. (2) 중간 block이 더 낮은 해상도의 token에서 동작하도록 하면서 다른 부분에서는 고해상도 처리를 유지하게 하는 ResNet 기반 token downsampling mechanism을 도입하여 latency를 줄였다. (3) sampling 중 denoiser의 초기 layer에서 얻은 visual signal을 활용하는 새로운 text encoder distillation approach를 제안했다. 실험적으로 NanoFLUX는 mobile device에서 약 2.5초 만에 $512 \\times 512$ 이미지를 생성하며, 고품질 on-device text-to-image generation의 실현 가능성을 입증한다."},{"id":"66319","en":"FlashBlock: Attention Caching for Efficient Long-Context Block Diffusion","ko":"FlashBlock: 효율적 장문맥 Block Diffusion을 위한 Attention 캐싱","authors":"Zhuokun Chen, Jianfei Cai, Bohan Zhuang","pos":"#3010","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=4jfuNNghPS","abs":"Generating long-form content, such as minute-long videos and extended texts, is increasingly important for modern generative models. Block diffusion improves inference efficiency via KV caching and block-wise causal inference and has been widely adopted in diffusion language models and video generation. However, in long-context settings, block diffusion still incurs substantial overhead from repeatedly computing attention over an ever-growing KV cache. We identify an underexplored property of block diffusion: cross-step redundancy of attention within a block. Our analysis shows that attention outputs from tokens outside the current block remain largely stable across diffusion steps, while block-internal attention varies significantly. Based on this observation, we propose FlashBlock, a cached block-external attention mechanism that reuses stable attention output, substantially reducing attention computation and KV cache access without modifying the diffusion process. Moreover, FlashBlock is orthogonal to sparse attention and can be combined as a complementary residual reuse strategy. When integrated, it substantially improves model accuracy under aggressive sparsification by offsetting much of the performance loss induced by sparsity. Experiments on diffusion language models and video generation demonstrate up to 1.44$\\times$ higher token throughput and up to 1.6$\\times$ reduction in attention time, with negligible impact on generation quality."},{"id":"61560","en":"SwiftPFN: Revisiting Row-Wise Attention–Only Tabular Foundation Models with Adaptive Early Exit","ko":"SwiftPFN: Adaptive Early Exit을 갖춘 Row-Wise Attention 전용 Tabular Foundation Models 재검토","authors":"Si-Yang Liu, Han-Jia Ye","pos":"#3316","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ottLtChHp2","abs":"<p>Tabular foundation models, exemplified by TabPFN, perform prediction via in-context learning, inferring test labels directly from labeled training examples. They have demonstrated competitive performance, particularly on small-to-medium datasets. However, recent tabular foundation models often improve accuracy with increasingly complex architectures, incurring higher inference cost and limiting practical deployment. In this work, we revisit the original TabPFN design and show that a lightweight row-wise attention–only backbone can remain highly competitive with two simple enhancements: a gated attention stabilization mechanism and a small set of learnable register tokens that provide global context and improve pretraining quality. The resulting model, SwiftPFN, supports both classification and regression, and is competitive with stronger tabular foundation models (e.g., TabPFN v2 and TabICL) while being more efficient at inference. For latency-sensitive serving, we further introduce an adaptive layer-wise early-exit mechanism that dynamically adjusts inference depth per sample. Experiments show that many samples can be reliably predicted using shallow layers, reducing average computation with negligible performance degradation. Overall, SwiftPFN enables efficient and anytime tabular in-context learning for practical deployments.</p>","absKo":"<p>TabPFN으로 대표되는 tabular foundation model은 in-context learning을 통해 예측을 수행하며, labeled training example로부터 test label을 직접 추론한다. 이들은 특히 중소형 데이터셋에서 경쟁력 있는 성능을 보여주었다. 그러나 최근의 tabular foundation model은 종종 점점 더 복잡한 architecture를 통해 정확도를 높이면서 inference 비용이 증가하고 실용적 배포가 제한된다. 본 연구에서는 원래 TabPFN 설계를 다시 검토하고, gated attention stabilization mechanism과 전역 context를 제공하고 pretraining 품질을 향상시키는 소수의 learnable register token이라는 두 가지 간단한 개선만으로도 가벼운 row-wise attention-only backbone이 여전히 매우 경쟁력 있을 수 있음을 보인다. 그 결과 모델 SwiftPFN은 classification과 regression을 모두 지원하며, TabPFN v2와 TabICL 같은 더 강력한 tabular foundation model과 경쟁적이면서도 inference 효율성이 더 높다. latency에 민감한 serving을 위해, 우리는 샘플별로 inference depth를 동적으로 조정하는 adaptive layer-wise early-exit mechanism을 추가로 도입한다. 실험 결과 많은 샘플이 얕은 layer만으로도 안정적으로 예측 가능하며, 성능 저하가 거의 없는 상태에서 평균 계산량을 줄일 수 있음을 보인다. 전반적으로 SwiftPFN은 실용적 배포를 위한 효율적이고 anytime tabular in-context learning을 가능하게 한다.</p>"},{"id":"63251","en":"MiniX: Mitigating Low-Rank Collapse and Attention Bottlenecks in Tabular Foundation Models","ko":"MiniX: 테이블형 Foundation 모델에서 저계수 붕괴와 어텐션 병목 완화","authors":"Yuanrui Wang, Xingxuan Zhang, Han Yu, Mingchao Hao, Gang Ren, hao yuan, Li Mao, Yunjia Zhang, Chun Yuan, Peng Cui","pos":"#3603","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=YjYPYg112A","abs":"Recent tabular foundation models routinely match or surpass strong tree ensembles and specialized deep architectures, yet their numeric embeddings remain a bottleneck. We diagnose a low-rank collapse induced by the prevalent linear+ID scheme and introduce RaBEL, a compact Radial Basis Embedding Layer that front-loads nonlinearity via localized RBF features. RaBEL increases shallow-layer effective rank and improves conditioning without deeper stacks; it is complementary to periodic mappings. We further identify a permutation-order pathology in bidirectional attention (feature$\\rightarrow$sample) and propose a reordered stack: sample-attention $\\rightarrow$ FFN $\\rightarrow$ feature-attention, ensuring column-level context precedes feature mixing and that all attention computations influence the readout. Combining both ideas yields MiniX, a 2M-parameter model that surpasses 7M-parameter TabPFN-v2 and 27M-parameter TabICL baselines on popular benchmarks while reducing training and inference cost. Our results highlight principled nonlinear embeddings and attention-order redesign as key enablers of accuracy and efficiency gains in tabular foundation models.","absKo":"최근의 tabular foundation model은 강력한 tree ensemble과 특화된 deep architecture와 대체로 견줄 만하거나 이를 능가하지만, 수치 embedding은 여전히 병목으로 남아 있다. 우리는 널리 사용되는 linear+ID scheme이 유발하는 low-rank collapse를 진단하고, localized RBF feature를 통해 비선형성을 앞단에서 주입하는 compact Radial Basis Embedding Layer인 RaBEL을 도입한다. RaBEL은 더 깊은 stack 없이 shallow layer의 effective rank를 높이고 conditioning을 개선하며, periodic mapping과는 상호 보완적이다. 또한 bidirectional attention(feature→sample)에서의 permutation-order pathology를 식별하고, sample-attention → FFN → feature-attention 순서의 재배열된 stack을 제안한다. 이를 통해 column-level context가 feature mixing보다 먼저 제공되고 모든 attention computation이 readout에 영향을 미치도록 보장한다. 이 두 아이디어를 결합하면 MiniX가 완성되는데, 이는 2M parameter model로서 인기 있는 benchmark에서 7M parameter TabPFN-v2와 27M parameter TabICL baseline을 능가하면서 training 및 inference 비용을 줄인다. 우리의 결과는 원리적인 비선형 embedding과 attention-order 재설계가 tabular foundation model의 정확도와 효율성 향상을 이끄는 핵심 요소임을 보여준다."},{"id":"62899","en":"InfoDLM: an Information-Adaptive Framework for Discrete Diffusion Language Model Pretraining","ko":"InfoDLM: 이산 확산 Language Model 사전학습을 위한 정보 적응형 프레임워크","authors":"Shirou Jing, Chunshu Wu, Chuan Liu, Arghavan Bahadorinejad, Feitong Qiao, Dongfang Liu, Tony Geng","pos":"#3608","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=c5fRyYtMos","abs":"<p>Diffusion language models (DLMs) can match or surpass similarly sized autoregressive language models on language understanding and reasoning. However, their mask-and-denoise pretraining relies on heuristic random masking, which fails to target the most informative tokens. Consequently, the model spends significant computational effort on redundant or trivial tokens. To address this, we propose InfoDLM, an adaptive DLM pretraining framework that reformulates mask selection as an active, feedback-driven process. InfoDLM targets tokens that offer the highest measurable information gain during mask selection. Specifically, we: (1) introduce a Trainable Information-Gain (TIG) signal to quantify information gain of each masking configuration; (2) develop a feedback mechanism that adapts the masking policy to the model’s evolving state with a maturity indicator; and (3) jointly optimize the DLM and masking policy through an interleaved training flow with minimal computational overhead. Across reasoning-oriented benchmarks, InfoDLM achieves up to 13\\% improvement in reasoning accuracy over a small variant of LLaDA under comparable pretraining budgets.</p>","absKo":"<p>Diffusion language model (DLM)은 language understanding과 reasoning에서 비슷한 크기의 autoregressive language model과 맞먹거나 이를 능가할 수 있다. 그러나 mask-and-denoise pretraining은 heuristic random masking에 의존하며, 이는 가장 informative한 token을 겨냥하지 못한다. 그 결과 모델은 중복되거나 사소한 token에 상당한 계산 자원을 소모한다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 mask selection을 active하고 feedback-driven한 과정으로 재구성하는 adaptive DLM pretraining framework인 InfoDLM을 제안한다. InfoDLM은 mask selection 동안 측정 가능한 information gain이 가장 높은 token을 대상으로 한다. 구체적으로 우리는 (1) 각 masking configuration의 information gain을 정량화하는 Trainable Information-Gain (TIG) signal을 도입하고, (2) maturity indicator를 통해 masking policy를 모델의 진화하는 상태에 적응시키는 feedback mechanism을 개발하며, (3) 최소한의 계산 오버헤드로 interleaved training flow를 통해 DLM과 masking policy를 공동 최적화한다. reasoning-oriented benchmark 전반에서 InfoDLM은 유사한 pretraining budget 하에서 작은 variant의 LLaDA 대비 reasoning accuracy를 최대 13\\% 향상시킨다.</p>"},{"id":"65062","en":"Moving Beyond Sparse Grounding with Complete Screen Parsing Supervision","ko":"완전한 화면 파싱 감독으로 Sparse Grounding을 넘어서기","authors":"A. Said Gurbuz, Sunghwan Hong, Ahmed Nassar, Marc Pollefeys, Peter Staar","pos":"#911","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=H8KE7sudq5","abs":"<p>Modern computer-use agents (CUA) must perceive a screen as a structured state, what elements are visible, where they are, and what text they contain, before they can reliably ground instructions and act. Yet, most available grounding datasets provide sparse supervision, with <em>insufficient</em> and <em>low-diversity</em> labels that annotate only a small subset of task-relevant elements per screen, which limits both coverage and generalization; moreover, practical deployment requires efficiency to enable low-latency, on-device use. We introduce <strong>ScreenParse</strong>, a large-scale dataset for <em>complete</em> screen parsing, with dense annotations of all visible UI elements (boxes, 55-class types, and text) across 771K web screenshots (21M elements). ScreenParse is generated by <strong>Webshot</strong>, an automated, scalable pipeline that renders diverse urls, extracts annotations and applies VLM-based relabeling and quality filtering. Using ScreenParse, we train <strong>ScreenVLM</strong>, a compact, 316M-parameter vision language model (VLM) that decodes a compact ScreenTag markup representation with a structure-aware loss that upweights structure-critical tokens. ScreenVLM substantially outperforms much larger foundation VLMs on dense parsing (e.g., 0.592 vs. 0.294 PageIoU on ScreenParse) and shows strong transfer to public benchmarks. Moreover, finetuning foundation VLMs on ScreenParse consistently improves their grounding performance, suggesting that dense screen supervision provides transferable structural priors for UI understanding. The dataset, model and code will be made publicly available.</p>"},{"id":"63138","en":"Long Grounded Thoughts: Synthesizing Grounded Visual Problems and Distilling Reasoning Chains at Scale","ko":"긴 근거 사고: 근거 기반 시각 문제 합성과 추론 사슬의 대규모 증류","authors":"David Acuna, Chao-Han Huck Yang, Yuntian Deng, Jaehun Jung, Ximing Lu, Prithviraj Ammanabrolu, Hyunwoo Kim, Yuan-Hong Liao, Yejin Choi","pos":"#913","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ZipucsUgc6","abs":"<p>Despite rapid progress, multimodal reasoning still lacks a systematic approach to synthesize large-scale vision-centric datasets beyond visual math. We introduce a framework able to synthesize vision-centric problems spanning diverse levels of complexity, and the resulting dataset with over 1M high-quality problems including: reasoning traces, preference data, and instruction prompts supporting SFT, offline and online RL.  Our vision-centric  synthesis framework uses a two-stage process focusing on: (1) generating diverse verifiable questions from existing images at scale, and (2) creating complex compositional visual problems by merging simpler questions.  Remarkably,  finetuning Qwen2.5-VL-7B on our data outperforms existing open-data baselines across evaluated vision-centric benchmarks, and our best configurations match or surpass strong closed-data models  such as MiMo-VL-7B-RL  on V*Bench, CV-Bench and MMStar-V. Notably, despite being entirely vision-centric, our data transfers positively to text-only reasoning (MMLU-Pro, +3.7%) and audio reasoning (MMAU, +1.32%), demonstrating its  effectiveness. Similarly, despite  containing no  embodied visual data, we observe notable gains (NiEH, +8.8%)  when evaluating open-ended  embodied QA. Lastly, we use our data to comprehensively analyze at scale (1M+) the entire VLM post-training pipeline showing that (i) SFT on high-quality data with cognitive behaviours on reasoning traces is essential to scale online RL, (ii) offline RL could match online RL’s performance while disaggregating compute demands, and, (iii)  SFT on high quality data also improve out-of-domain, cross-modality transfer.</p>","absKo":"<p>빠른 진전에도 불구하고, multimodal reasoning은 visual math를 넘어 대규모 vision-centric dataset을 체계적으로 합성하는 방법이 여전히 부족하다. 우리는 다양한 복잡도 수준을 아우르는 vision-centric problem을 합성할 수 있는 framework와, reasoning trace, preference data, SFT, offline 및 online RL을 지원하는 instruction prompt를 포함한 100만 개 이상의 고품질 문제로 구성된 dataset을 소개한다. 우리의 vision-centric synthesis framework는 다음 두 단계에 기반한다: (1) 기존 이미지로부터 다양한 검증 가능한 질문을 대규모로 생성하고, (2) 더 단순한 질문들을 결합해 복합적인 compositional visual problem을 만드는 것이다. 놀랍게도, 우리의 데이터로 Qwen2.5-VL-7B를 finetuning하면 평가한 vision-centric benchmark 전반에서 기존 open-data baseline을 능가하며, 최상의 설정은 V*Bench, CV-Bench, MMStar-V에서 MiMo-VL-7B-RL과 같은 강력한 closed-data model과 맞먹거나 이를 능가한다. 특히, 데이터가 전적으로 vision-centric임에도 불구하고 text-only reasoning (MMLU-Pro, +3.7%)과 audio reasoning (MMAU, +1.32%)에도 긍정적으로 transfer되어 그 효과성을 보여준다. 마찬가지로 embodied visual data를 전혀 포함하지 않음에도, open-ended embodied QA를 평가할 때도 유의미한 향상(NiEH, +8.8%)을 관찰했다. 마지막으로, 우리는 이 데이터를 사용해 100만+ 규모로 전체 VLM post-training pipeline을 종합적으로 분석했다. 그 결과, (i) reasoning trace에서 cognitive behavior를 담은 고품질 data에 대한 SFT가 online RL을 확장하는 데 필수적이며, (ii) offline RL은 compute 요구를 분산시키면서 online RL의 성능과 동등할 수 있고, (iii) 고품질 data에 대한 SFT는 out-of-domain, cross-modality transfer도 향상시킨다는 점을 보였다.</p>"},{"id":"61295","en":"Test-Time Anchoring for Discrete Diffusion Posterior Sampling","ko":"Discrete Diffusion Posterior Sampling을 위한 Test-Time Anchoring","authors":"Litu Rout, Andreas Lugmayr, Yasamin Jafarian, Srivatsan Varadharajan, Constantine Caramanis, Sanjay Shakkottai, Ira Kemelmacher-Shlizerman","pos":"#2500","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=rdWE5ol3ps","abs":"<p>While continuous diffusion models have achieved remarkable success, discrete diffusion offers a unified framework for jointly modeling text and images. Beyond unification, discrete diffusion provides faster inference, finer control, and principled training-free guidance, making it well-suited for posterior sampling. Existing approaches to posterior sampling using discrete diffusion face severe challenges: derivative-free guidance yields sparse signals, continuous relaxations limit applicability, and split Gibbs samplers suffer from the curse of dimensionality. To overcome these limitations, we introduce Anchored Posterior Sampling (APS), built on two key innovations: <em>quantized expectation</em> for gradient-like guidance in discrete embedding space, and <em>anchored remasking</em> for adaptive decoding. APS achieves state-of-the-art performance among discrete diffusion samplers on both linear and nonlinear inverse problems across the standard image benchmarks. We demonstrate the generality of APS through training-free stylization and text-guided editing. We further apply APS to a large-scale diffusion language model, showing consistent improvement in question answering.</p>","absKo":"<p>연속 diffusion model이 놀라운 성공을 거두었지만, discrete diffusion은 text와 image를 함께 모델링하는 통합된 framework를 제공합니다. 이러한 통합을 넘어, discrete diffusion은 더 빠른 inference, 더 정교한 control, 그리고 원리적인 training-free guidance를 제공하므로 posterior sampling에 특히 적합합니다. 그러나 discrete diffusion을 이용한 기존 posterior sampling 방법들은 심각한 한계에 직면합니다. derivative-free guidance는 신호가 희소하고, continuous relaxation은 적용 가능 범위를 제한하며, split Gibbs sampler는 curse of dimensionality에 취약합니다. 이러한 한계를 극복하기 위해, 우리는 Anchored Posterior Sampling (APS)를 제안합니다. APS는 두 가지 핵심 혁신 위에 구축됩니다: discrete embedding space에서 gradient와 유사한 guidance를 제공하는 <em>quantized expectation</em>과 적응형 decoding을 위한 <em>anchored remasking</em>입니다. APS는 표준 image benchmark 전반의 linear 및 nonlinear inverse problem에서 discrete diffusion sampler 중 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성합니다. 또한 training-free stylization과 text-guided editing을 통해 APS의 일반성을 입증합니다. 더 나아가 APS를 대규모 diffusion language model에 적용하여 question answering에서 일관된 성능 향상을 보임을 확인합니다.</p>"},{"id":"63538","en":"UDM-GRPO: Stable and Efficient Group Relative Policy Optimization for Uniform Discrete Diffusion Models","ko":"UDM-GRPO: 균일 이산 확산 모델을 위한 안정적이고 효율적인 그룹 상대 정책 최적화","authors":"Jiaqi Wang, Haoge Deng, Ting Pan, Yang Liu, Chengyuan Wang, Fan Zhang, Yonggang Qi, Xinlong Wang","pos":"#109","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=WJcFtJriqv","abs":"Uniform Discrete Diffusion (UDM) has recently emerged as a promising paradigm for discrete generative modeling; however, its integration with reinforcement learning remains largely unexplored. We observe that naively adapting GRPO to UDM leads to unstable training and marginal performance. To address this, we propose \\Ours, the first framework that integrates UDM with RL. Our method is guided by two key insights: (i) treating the final clean sample, rather than intermediate predicted sample, as the action provides more accurate and stable optimization signals; and (ii) adopting the forward process to reconstruct the training trajectories helps the model learn probability paths that are more consistent with pretraining. For efficiency, we introduce Reduction-Step and CFG-Free training strategies. \\Ours significantly improves the performance of the base model across multiple T2I tasks. Notably, GenEval accuracy improves from $69\\%$ to $96\\%$ and PickScore increases from $20.46$ to $23.81$, achieving state-of-the-art performance in both continuous and discrete settings. On the OCR benchmark, accuracy improves from $4\\%$ to $57\\%$, further validating the effectiveness and generalization capability of our method.","absKo":"Uniform Discrete Diffusion (UDM)은 최근 유망한 discrete generative modeling 패러다임으로 부상했지만, reinforcement learning과의 통합은 아직 거의 탐구되지 않았다. 우리는 GRPO를 UDM에 단순 적용하면 training이 불안정해지고 성능 향상도 미미하다는 점을 관찰했다. 이를 해결하기 위해, UDM과 RL을 통합하는 최초의 framework인 \\Ours를 제안한다. 우리의 방법은 두 가지 핵심 통찰에 의해 이끌어진다: (i) 중간에 예측된 sample이 아니라 최종 clean sample을 action으로 간주하면 더 정확하고 안정적인 optimization signal을 제공한다는 점; (ii) forward process를 채택하여 training trajectory를 reconstruct하면 pretraining과 더 일관된 probability path를 모델이 학습하는 데 도움이 된다는 점이다. 효율성을 위해 Reduction-Step과 CFG-Free training strategy를 도입한다. \\Ours는 여러 T2I task 전반에서 base model의 성능을 크게 향상시킨다. 특히 GenEval accuracy는 $69\\%$에서 $96\\%$로, PickScore는 $20.46$에서 $23.81$로 향상되어, continuous setting과 discrete setting 모두에서 state-of-the-art performance를 달성한다. OCR benchmark에서는 accuracy가 $4\\%$에서 $57\\%$로 향상되어, 우리의 방법의 효과성과 일반화 능력을 추가로 입증한다."},{"id":"65731","en":"$E^2$PO: Embedding-perturbed Exploration Preference Optimization for Flow Models","ko":"$E^2$PO: Flow 모델을 위한 임베딩 섭동 탐색 선호 최적화","authors":"Sujie Hu, Chubin Chen, Jiashu Zhu, Jiahong Wu, Xiangxiang Chu, Xiu Li","pos":"#1109","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Ai4vdy80p5","abs":"Recent advancements have established Reinforcement Learning (RL) as a pivotal paradigm for aligning generative models with human intent. However, group-based optimization frameworks (e.g., GRPO) face a critical limitation: *the rapid decay of intra-group variance*. As the distinctiveness among samples within a group diminishes, the variance approaches zero. This eliminates the very learning signal required for optimization, rendering the process unstable and forcing the policy into *premature stagnation or reward hacking*. Existing strategies, such as varying the initial noise or increasing group sizes, often fail to address this fundamental issue, resulting in *training instability or diminishing returns*. To overcome these challenges, we propose **$E$mbedding-perturbed $E$xploration Preference Optimization ($E^2$PO)**, a novel framework that sustains optimization through embedding-level perturbation. Our method introduces structured, embedding-level perturbations within sample groups, guaranteeing a robust variance that preserves the discriminative signal throughout the training process. Extensive experiments demonstrate that our approach significantly outperforms state-of-the-art baselines, achieving a more faithful alignment with human preference."},{"id":"65241","en":"Predicting Future KV Utility: Global Combinatorial Optimization for Task-Agnostic KV Cache Eviction","ko":"미래 KV 유용성 예측: Task-Agnostic KV Cache 제거를 위한 전역 조합 최적화","authors":"Ziyao Tang, Pengkun Jiao, Xinhang Chen, LiuWei Liu, Shiyong Li, Jingjing Chen","pos":"#1801","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=FQLxcBsKIb","abs":"<p>Given the quadratic complexity of attention, KV cache eviction is vital to accelerate model inference. Current KV cache eviction methods typically rely on instantaneous heuristic metrics, implicitly assuming that score magnitudes are consistent proxies for importance across all heads. However, this overlooks the heterogeneity in predictive fidelity across attention heads. While certain heads prioritize the \\textit{instantaneous contribution} of tokens, others are dedicated to capturinglong-horizon utility. In this paper, we propose that optimal budget allocation should be governed by the marginal utility in preserving long-term semantic information. Based on this insight, we propose LU-KV, a novel framework that optimizes head-level budget allocation through a convex-hull relaxation and a marginal-utility-based greedy solver to achieve near-optimal precision. Furthermore, we implement a data-driven offline profiling protocol to facilitate the practical deployment of LU-KV.</p>"},{"id":"60788","en":"CoFrGeNet: Continued Fraction Architectures for Language Generation","ko":"CoFrGeNet: 언어 생성을 위한 Continued Fraction Architecture","authors":"Amit Dhurandhar, Vijil Chenthamarakshan, Dennis Wei, Tejaswini Pedapati, Karthikeyan Natesan Ramamurthy, Rahul Nair","pos":"#2215","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=wjc6oz63WL","abs":"<p>Transformers are arguably the preferred architecture for language generation. In this paper, inspired by continued fractions, we introduce a new function class for generative modeling. The architecture family implementing this function class is named CoFrGeNets - Continued Fraction Generative Networks. We design novel architectural components based on this function class that can replace Multi-head Attention and Feed-Forward Networks in Transformer blocks while requiring much fewer parameters. We derive custom gradient formulations to optimize the proposed components more accurately and efficiently than using standard PyTorch-based gradients. Our components are a plug-in replacement requiring little change in training or inference procedures that have already been put in place for Transformer-based models thus making our approach easy to incorporate in large industrial workflows. We experiment on two very different transformer architectures GPT2-xl (1.5B) and Llama3 (3.2B), where the former we pre-train on OpenWebText and GneissWeb, while the latter we pre-train on the docling data mix which consists of nine different datasets. Results show that the performance on downstream classification, Q&amp;amp; A, reasoning and text understanding tasks of our models is competitive and sometimes even superior to the original models with two thirds to half the parameters and shorter pre-training time. We believe that future implementations customized to hardware will further bring out the true potential of our architectures.</p>","absKo":"<p>Transformer는 언어 생성에 있어 사실상 선호되는 architecture로 여겨진다. 본 논문에서는 continued fraction에서 영감을 받아 generative modeling을 위한 새로운 function class를 도입한다. 이 function class를 구현하는 architecture family는 CoFrGeNets - Continued Fraction Generative Networks라 명명한다. 우리는 이 function class에 기반한 새로운 architectural component를 설계했으며, 이는 Transformer block의 Multi-head Attention과 Feed-Forward Network를 대체하면서 훨씬 적은 parameter만을 필요로 한다. 또한 standard PyTorch 기반 gradient를 사용하는 것보다 제안한 component를 더 정확하고 효율적으로 최적화하기 위한 맞춤형 gradient formulation을 유도한다. 우리의 component는 plug-in replacement로서, Transformer-based model에 이미 적용되어 있는 training 또는 inference procedure를 거의 변경하지 않고 사용할 수 있으므로, 대규모 산업 워크플로에 쉽게 통합할 수 있다. 우리는 매우 다른 두 가지 Transformer architecture인 GPT2-xl (1.5B)과 Llama3 (3.2B)에서 실험했으며, 전자는 OpenWebText와 GneissWeb으로 pre-train했고, 후자는 아홉 개의 서로 다른 dataset으로 구성된 docling data mix로 pre-train했다. 결과는 downstream classification, Q&amp;amp; A, reasoning, text understanding task에서 우리의 model이 original model과 경쟁적이며, 때로는 parameter를 2/3에서 절반 수준만 사용하고 pre-training time도 더 짧음에도 더 우수함을 보여준다. 우리는 hardware에 맞게 customized된 future implementation이 우리의 architecture의 진정한 잠재력을 더욱 끌어낼 것이라 믿는다.</p>"},{"id":"63228","en":"Stabilizing Reinforcement Learning for Diffusion Language Models","ko":"Diffusion 언어 모델을 위한 강화학습 안정화","authors":"Jianyuan Zhong, Wang Kaibo, Ding Ding, Zijin Feng, Haoli Bai, Yang Xiang, Jiacheng Sun, Qiang Xu","pos":"#2502","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=YvGtYoFyud","abs":"<p>Diffusion Large Language Models (dLLMs) often exhibit severe instability during Group Relative Policy Optimization (GRPO) training, limiting the effectiveness of reinforcement learning for improving reasoning capabilities. In dLLMs, the importance ratios used by GRPO are derived from finite-sample estimates rather than exact likelihoods, making them inherently noisy. In this paper, we show that GRPO is highly sensitive to this noise, which drives training instability. Through theoretical analysis and empirical evidence, we identify a self-reinforcing instability loop in which noisy importance ratios induce gradient spikes and policy drift, further amplifying future importance ratio estimation variance. To address this issue, we propose StableDRL, a novel reinforcement learning framework for dLLMs. StableDRL stabilizes training via (i) unconditional clipping to suppress outlier-induced gradient spikes, and (ii) self-normalization to constrain gradients within the convex hull of per-sample updates. We further extend StableDRL to block-wise diffusion models via a staircase attention mechanism. StableDRL is the first method that enables stable, full-parameter reinforcement learning for dLLMs. It achieves the state-of-the-art performance, outperforming prior best full-attention baselines by 6% on MATH500 and block-diffusion baselines by 25.6% on AIME.</p>","absKo":"<p>Diffusion Large Language Model (dLLM)은 Group Relative Policy Optimization (GRPO) training 동안 심각한 불안정성을 자주 보이며, 이로 인해 reasoning capability 향상을 위한 reinforcement learning의 효과가 제한된다. dLLM에서 GRPO가 사용하는 importance ratio는 정확한 likelihood가 아니라 finite-sample estimate에서 유도되므로 본질적으로 noisy하다. 본 논문에서는 GRPO가 이 noise에 매우 민감하며, 이것이 training instability를 유발함을 보인다. 이론적 분석과 경험적 증거를 통해, noisy importance ratio가 gradient spike와 policy drift를 유도하고, 이것이 다시 향후 importance ratio estimation variance를 더욱 증폭시키는 자기강화적 불안정성 루프를 식별한다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해 우리는 dLLM을 위한 새로운 reinforcement learning framework인 StableDRL을 제안한다. StableDRL은 (i) outlier로 인한 gradient spike를 억제하기 위한 unconditional clipping, (ii) per-sample update의 convex hull 내로 gradient를 제한하는 self-normalization을 통해 training을 안정화한다. 또한 StableDRL을 staircase attention mechanism을 통해 block-wise diffusion model로 확장한다. StableDRL은 dLLM에 대해 안정적인 full-parameter reinforcement learning을 가능하게 하는 첫 번째 방법이다. 이는 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성하며, MATH500에서 기존 최고 full-attention baseline보다 6%, AIME에서 block-diffusion baseline보다 25.6% 더 우수하다.</p>"},{"id":"60951","en":"Spectral Guidance for Flexible and Efficient Control of Diffusion Models","ko":"Diffusion Model의 유연하고 효율적인 제어를 위한 Spectral Guidance","authors":"Gabriel Moreira, Manuel Marques, Joao Costeira, Chenyan Xiong","pos":"#2503","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=v63OyiRoS2","abs":"We introduce Spectral Guidance, a framework for controlling diffusion models by leveraging the intrinsic geometry of the generative process. As data is progressively corrupted by noise, only a small number of features remain informative for control. We characterize them as the singular functions of a conditional expectation operator and show that they can be learned via a self-supervised objective. Once recovered, this basis enables the projection of arbitrary guidance signals, such as labels, CLIP embeddings, or masks, directly onto the sampling trajectory. This approach allows for stable, high-fidelity control without retraining or denoiser backpropagation during sampling. Empirically, we improve conditional accuracy on CIFAR-10 by 37 percentage points over the strongest training-free baseline while offering $4\\times$ faster sampling. Moreover, the same representations that support label and CLIP guidance also enable spatial control, such as mask-based guidance, without auxiliary models. Finally, our framework reveals a phase transition in the generative process, pinpointing the optimal time window for effective guidance.","absKo":"우리는 생성 과정의 intrinsic geometry를 활용하여 diffusion model을 제어하는 프레임워크인 Spectral Guidance를 소개한다. 데이터가 노이즈에 의해 점진적으로 손상됨에 따라, 제어에 유용한 특징은 소수만 남는다. 우리는 이를 conditional expectation operator의 singular functions로 규정하고, self-supervised objective를 통해 학습될 수 있음을 보인다. 일단 복원되면, 이 basis는 label, CLIP embedding, mask와 같은 임의의 guidance signal을 sampling trajectory 위에 직접 projection할 수 있게 한다. 이 접근법은 sampling 중 retraining이나 denoiser backpropagation 없이도 안정적이고 high-fidelity control을 가능하게 한다. 실험적으로, 우리는 CIFAR-10에서 conditional accuracy를 가장 강력한 training-free baseline 대비 37 percentage points 향상시키면서 $4\\times$ 더 빠른 sampling을 제공한다. 또한 label 및 CLIP guidance를 지원하는 동일한 representation은 auxiliary model 없이도 mask-based guidance와 같은 spatial control을 가능하게 한다. 마지막으로, 우리의 framework는 generative process에서 phase transition을 드러내며, 효과적인 guidance를 위한 최적의 time window를 정확히 짚어낸다."},{"id":"61004","en":"Physics-informed diffusion models in spectral space","ko":"스펙트럴 공간의 Physics-informed Diffusion Model","authors":"Davide Gallon, Philippe von Wurstemberger, Patrick Cheridito, Arnulf Jentzen","pos":"#2510","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ue7XmbJ2QZ","abs":"<p>We propose a methodology that combines generative latent diffusion models with physics-informed machine learning to generate solutions of parametric partial differential equations (PDEs) conditioned on partial observations, which includes, in particular, forward and inverse PDE problems. We learn the joint distribution of PDE parameters and solutions via a diffusion process in a latent space of scaled spectral representations, where Gaussian noise corresponds to functions with controlled regularity. This spectral formulation enables significant dimensionality reduction compared to grid-based diffusion models and ensures that the induced process in function space remains within a class of functions for which the PDE operators are well defined. Building on diffusion posterior sampling, we enforce physics-informed constraints and measurement conditions during inference, applying Adam-based updates at each diffusion step. We evaluate the proposed approach on Poisson, Helmholtz, and incompressible Navier--Stokes equations, demonstrating improved accuracy and computational efficiency compared with existing diffusion-based PDE solvers, which are state of the art for sparse observations. Code is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/PISD-32A0/.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 generative latent diffusion models와 physics-informed machine learning을 결합해, partial observations로 조건화된 parametric partial differential equations (PDEs)의 해를 생성하는 방법론을 제안한다. 이는 특히 forward 및 inverse PDE 문제를 포함한다. 우리는 scaled spectral representations의 latent space에서 diffusion process를 통해 PDE parameters와 solutions의 joint distribution을 학습하며, 이때 Gaussian noise는 regularity가 제어된 functions에 대응한다. 이러한 spectral formulation은 grid-based diffusion models에 비해 차원을 크게 줄여 주고, 유도되는 function space상의 process가 PDE operators가 잘 정의되는 함수 클래스 안에 머물도록 보장한다. diffusion posterior sampling을 기반으로, inference 시 physics-informed constraints와 measurement conditions를 강제하며, 각 diffusion step마다 Adam-based updates를 적용한다. 우리는 Poisson, Helmholtz, 그리고 incompressible Navier--Stokes equations에서 제안한 접근법을 평가했으며, sparse observations에 대해 state of the art인 기존 diffusion-based PDE solvers보다 더 나은 정확도와 계산 효율을 보임을 확인했다. 코드는 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/PISD-32A0/ 에서 제공된다.</p>"},{"id":"64836","en":"OneSearch: A Preliminary Exploration of the Unified End-to-End Generative Framework for E-commerce Search","ko":"OneSearch: E-commerce 검색을 위한 통합 End-to-End 생성 프레임워크의 예비 탐구","authors":"Ben Chen, Xian Guo, Siyuan Wang, Zihan Liang, Yufei Ma, Yue Lv, Chenyi Lei, Yuqing DING, Wenwu Ou, Han Li, Kun Gai","pos":"#2512","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=JKGgHY9FKa","abs":"<p>Traditional e-commerce search systems employ multi-stage cascading architectures (MCA) that suffer from fragmented computation and optimization objective collisions across stages, ultimately limiting their performance ceiling.  We propose OneSearch, the first industrial-deployed end-to-end generative framework for e-commerce search, featuring three key innovations: (1) Keyword-enhanced Hierarchical Quantization Encoding (KHQE) to preserve hierarchical semantics and distinctive item attributes while maintaining strong query-item relevance constraints;  (2) multi-view user behavior sequence injection that constructs behavior-driven user IDs and incorporates both explicit short-term and implicit long-term sequences;  and (3) a Preference-Aware Reward System (PARS) with multi-stage supervised fine-tuning and adaptive reward-weighted ranking to capture fine-grained user preferences.  Extensive offline evaluations demonstrate its superior performance, while online A/B tests achieve statistically significant improvements: +1.67\\% item CTR, +2.40\\% buyer, and +3.22\\% order volume. OneSearch reduces operational expenditure by 75.40\\%, improves Model FLOPs Utilization from 3.26\\% to 27.32\\%, and has been successfully deployed across multiple search scenarios in TEST, serving millions of users daily. Code and datasets will be made publicly available.</p>"},{"id":"65578","en":"Multi-Objective Protein Design via Memory-Aware Test-Time Scaling in Diffusion Models","ko":"Diffusion Model에서 메모리 인지 Test-Time 스케일링을 통한 다목적 단백질 설계","authors":"Ming Yang, Xin Zheng, Yi Li, YIZHEN ZHENG, Huan Yee Koh, Yanqing Guo, Xiaofeng Cao, Shirui Pan","pos":"#2515","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=CG4TVesbcR","abs":"<p>Multi-objective protein design is essential for meeting the complex demands of synthetic biology. To adapt to shifting multi-functional targets without the prohibitive cost of retraining, test-time scaling has emerged as a flexible, training-free alternative.  However, current test-time diffusion methods face critical challenges: i) ineffective learning from interaction history leading to repetitive design errors, ii) over-reliance on successful cases as the reward signal, and iii) difficulties in balancing multi-objective functional trade-offs . To address these limitations, we propose MoMST, a framework for Multi-objective protein design via Memory-aware Self-contrastive learning with Test-time scaling in diffusion models. At test time, we develop a memory bank to extract generalizable reasoning experience from historical iterations. Building on this powerful experience learner, we derive rich residue-level relative preference signals from both successful and failed cases via self-contrastive learning for guiding protein generation. To ensure balance among competing multi-objective functions, we present an inference-time Pareto alignment strategy to resolve objective conflicts. Evaluations on both single-objective and complex multi-objective tasks demonstrate that MoMST exhibits remarkable performance.</p>"},{"id":"61657","en":"Contrastive Diffusion Alignment: Learning Structured Latents for Controllable Generation","ko":"Contrastive Diffusion Alignment: 제어 가능한 생성을 위한 구조화 잠재 표현 학습","authors":"Ruchi Sandilya, Sumaira Perez, Charles Lynch, Lindsay Victoria, Benjamin Zebley, Derrick Buchanan, Mahendra Bhati, Nolan Williams, Timothy Spellman, FAITH GUNNING, Conor Liston, Logan Grosenick","pos":"#2600","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=o2H3TE1F0g","abs":"<p>Diffusion models excel at generation, but their latent spaces are high dimensional and not explicitly organized for interpretation or control. We introduce ConDA (Contrastive Diffusion Alignment), a plug-and-play geometry layer that applies contrastive learning to pretrained diffusion latents using auxiliary variables (e.g., time, stimulation parameters, facial action units). ConDA learns a low-dimensional embedding whose directions align with underlying dynamical factors, consistent with recent contrastive learning results on structured and disentangled representations. In this embedding, simple nonlinear trajectories support smooth interpolation, extrapolation, and counterfactual editing while rendering remains in the original diffusion space. ConDA separates editing and rendering by lifting embedding trajectories back to diffusion latents with a neighborhood-preserving kNN decoder and is robust across inversion solvers. Across fluid dynamics, neural calcium imaging, therapeutic neurostimulation, facial expression dynamics, and monkey motor cortex activity, ConDA yields more interpretable and controllable latent structure than linear traversals and conditioning-based baselines, indicating that diffusion latents encode dynamics-relevant structure that can be exploited by an explicit contrastive geometry layer.</p>","absKo":"<p>diffusion model은 생성에서 뛰어나지만, 그 latent space는 고차원이면서 해석이나 제어를 위해 명시적으로 조직되어 있지 않습니다. 우리는 pretrained diffusion latent에 auxiliary variable(예: time, stimulation parameter, facial action unit)을 사용해 contrastive learning을 적용하는 plug-and-play geometry layer인 ConDA(Contrastive Diffusion Alignment)를 소개합니다. ConDA는 구조화되고 disentangled된 representation에 대한 최근 contrastive learning 결과와 일치하는 방식으로, underlying dynamical factor와 방향이 정렬되는 저차원 embedding을 학습합니다. 이 embedding에서는 단순한 nonlinear trajectory가 매끄러운 interpolation, extrapolation, counterfactual editing을 지원하는 반면, rendering은 원래 diffusion space에서 유지됩니다. ConDA는 neighborhood-preserving kNN decoder를 사용해 embedding trajectory를 diffusion latent로 되돌림으로써 editing과 rendering을 분리하며, inversion solver 전반에서 견고합니다. fluid dynamics, neural calcium imaging, therapeutic neurostimulation, facial expression dynamics, monkey motor cortex activity 전반에서 ConDA는 linear traversal 및 conditioning 기반 baseline보다 더 해석 가능하고 제어 가능한 latent structure를 제공하며, diffusion latent가 명시적 contrastive geometry layer로 활용할 수 있는 dynamics-relevant structure를 인코딩함을 보여줍니다.</p>"},{"id":"63079","en":"Diffusion Bridge or Flow Matching? A Unifying Framework and Comparative Analysis","ko":"Diffusion Bridge인가 Flow Matching인가? 통합 프레임워크와 비교 분석","authors":"Kaizhen Zhu, Mokai Pan, Zhechuan Yu, Jingya Wang, Jingyi Yu, Ye Shi","pos":"#2602","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=aIFgQusnPy","abs":"Diffusion Bridge and Flow Matching have both demonstrated compelling empirical performance in transformation between arbitrary distributions. However, there remains confusion about which approach is generally preferable, and the substantial discrepancies in their modeling assumptions and practical implementations have hindered a unified theoretical account of their relative merits. We have, for the first time, provided a unified theoretical and experimental validation of these two models. We recast their frameworks through the lens of Stochastic Optimal Control and prove that the cost function of the Diffusion Bridge is lower, guiding the system toward more stable and natural trajectories. Simultaneously, from the perspective of Optimal Transport, interpolation coefficients $t$ and $1-t$ of Flow Matching become increasingly ineffective when the training data size is reduced. To corroborate these theoretical claims, we propose a novel, powerful architecture for Diffusion Bridge built on a latent Transformer, and implement a Flow Matching model with the same structure to enable a fair performance comparison in various experiments. Comprehensive experiments are conducted across Image Restoration, Translation, and Style Transfer tasks, systematically varying both the distributional discrepancy (different difficulty) and the training data size. Extensive empirical results align perfectly with our theoretical predictions and allow us to delineate the respective advantages and disadvantages of these two models. Our code is available at \\url{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/DBFM-3E8E/}.","absKo":"Diffusion Bridge와 Flow Matching은 모두 임의의 분포 사이 변환에서 인상적인 실증 성능을 보여 왔다. 그러나 일반적으로 어느 접근이 더 바람직한지에 대한 혼란이 남아 있으며, 모델링 가정과 실제 구현의 상당한 차이로 인해 두 방법의 상대적 장점에 대한 통합된 이론적 설명이 부족했다. 우리는 이 두 모델에 대해 처음으로 통합된 이론적 및 실험적 검증을 제시한다. 우리는 Stochastic Optimal Control의 관점으로 이들의 프레임워크를 재해석하고, Diffusion Bridge의 cost function이 더 낮다는 것을 증명하여 시스템이 더 안정적이고 자연스러운 trajectory를 따르도록 유도함을 보인다. 동시에 Optimal Transport의 관점에서 보면, 학습 데이터 크기가 줄어들수록 Flow Matching의 interpolation coefficient $t$와 $1-t$는 점점 비효율적이 된다. 이러한 이론적 주장을 뒷받침하기 위해, 우리는 latent Transformer에 기반한 Diffusion Bridge용의 새롭고 강력한 아키텍처를 제안하고, 공정한 성능 비교를 위해 동일한 구조의 Flow Matching 모델도 구현한다. Image Restoration, Translation, Style Transfer task 전반에 걸쳐, 분포 차이(난이도 차이)와 학습 데이터 크기를 모두 변화시키며 포괄적인 실험을 수행한다. 광범위한 실증 결과는 우리의 이론적 예측과 완벽하게 부합하며, 두 모델의 각각의 장단점을 명확히 구분하게 해준다. 코드: \\url{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/DBFM-3E8E/}.</p>"},{"id":"65624","en":"EigenCache: Rethinking Diffusion Acceleration as Covariance-Optimal Forecasting and Submodular Information Allocation","ko":"EigenCache: Diffusion 가속을 공분산 최적 예측 및 서브모듈러 정보 할당으로 재고하기","authors":"Chenyang Xu, Dezhen Wang, Lin Chen, Kepeng Lin, Hao Wang","pos":"#2604","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=BjMsVqss9N","abs":"<p>Accelerating diffusion models via feature caching has evolved from static reuse to polynomial extrapolation, yet current \"cache-then-forecast\" strategies remain limited by rigid, hand-crafted approximation families (e.g., Taylor or Hermite bases) that often misalign with the complex, layer-specific non-stationarity of generative feature dynamics. This paper introduces EigenCache, a theoretically grounded framework that re-frames acceleration as a problem of covariance learning and experimental design. By modeling feature trajectories as time-indexed stochastic processes governed by learnable temporal kernels, we demonstrate that the statistically optimal feature predictor (Minimum Mean Squared Error) is the Gaussian Process posterior mean (Kriging), which strictly generalizes and outperforms previous fixed-basis expansions. Crucially, this probabilistic formulation couples prediction with uncertainty quantification via a closed-form variance certificate. Leveraging this, we derive an information-theoretic scheduling algorithm that selects computation anchors by maximizing the log-determinant of the posterior covariance—a submodular objective that admits a provably near-optimal greedy solution. EigenCache thus provides a unified, training-free foundation for efficient inference, offering not only superior reconstruction accuracy but also a rigorous mechanism for robust, uncertainty-aware compute allocation.</p>"},{"id":"66512","en":"Exploring and Exploiting Stability in Latent Flow Matching","ko":"잠재 Flow Matching에서 안정성 탐구 및 활용","authors":"Rania Briq, Michael Kamp, Ohad Fried, Sarel Cohen, Stefan Kesselheim","pos":"#2606","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=33xuIDnp4u","abs":"<p>In this work, we show that Latent Flow-Matching (LFM) models are robust to different types of perturbations, including data reduction and model capacity shrinkage. We characterize this stability by their tendency to generate similar outputs under identical noise seeds. We provide a perspective relating this phenomenon to flow matching theory, which indicates that this stability is inherent to the FM objective. We further exploit this stability to derive practical algorithms for more efficient training and inference. Concretely, first, we show that by training LFM models on significantly reduced datasets, the performance does not degrade perceptually or quantitatively. This yields multiple advantages, such as reducing training time by converging faster under limited compute budget, and alleviating annotation effort when training conditional models. Second, LFM stability under architectural shrinkage gives rise to a two-model coarse-to-fine approach, one using a light-weight architecture for the first phase of the FM trajectory, and one with higher capacity for the second, thereby reducing the inference cost substantially. To determine which samples are informative, we introduce three sample-scoring criteria and evaluate them under standard metrics for generative models. Our results are thoroughly evaluated on multiple datasets, demonstrating the practical advantage of this stability, including data saving and a more than two-fold inference speedup while generating comparable outputs.</p>"},{"id":"63816","en":"General and Efficient Steering of Unconditional Diffusion Models","ko":"unconditional diffusion 모델의 일반적이고 효율적인 steering","authors":"Qingsong Wang, Misha Belkin, Yusu Wang","pos":"#2609","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=TU63jmFEWN","abs":"<p>Conditioning unconditional diffusion models typically requires either retraining with conditional inputs or per-step gradient computations (e.g., classifier-based guidance), both of which incur substantial computational overhead. We present a general recipe for efficiently steering unconditional diffusion <em>without gradient guidance during inference</em>, enabling fast controllable generation. Our approach is built on two observations about diffusion model structure: <strong>Noise Alignment</strong>: even in early, highly corrupted stages, coarse semantic steering is possible using a lightweight, offline-computed guidance signal, avoiding any per-step or per-sample gradients. <strong>Transferable concept vectors</strong>: a concept direction in activation space once learned through Recursive Feature Machines (RFMs)  transfers across both <em>timesteps</em> and <em>samples</em>; the same fixed steering vector learned near clean time remains effective when injected at intermediate noise levels for every generation trajectory, providing refined conditional control with efficiency.  Experiments on CIFAR-10, ImageNet, and CelebA demonstrate improved accuracy/quality relative to gradient-based guidance, while achieving significant inference speedups.</p>","absKo":"<p>unconditional diffusion model을 conditioning하는 일은 일반적으로 conditional input으로 재학습하거나 단계별 gradient 계산(예: classifier-based guidance)을 필요로 하며, 둘 다 상당한 계산 오버헤드를 유발한다. 우리는 <em>inference during inference</em>에서 gradient guidance 없이 unconditional diffusion을 효율적으로 steering하기 위한 일반적인 recipe를 제시하며, 빠르고 controllable한 generation을 가능하게 한다. 우리의 접근은 diffusion model 구조에 관한 두 가지 관찰에 기반한다: <strong>Noise Alignment</strong>: 초기의 매우 노이즈가 큰 단계에서도, 경량의 offline-computed guidance signal을 사용하여 coarse semantic steering이 가능하며, 단계별 또는 sample별 gradient를 전혀 피할 수 있다. <strong>Transferable concept vectors</strong>: Recursive Feature Machines(RFMs)를 통해 한 번 학습된 activation space의 concept direction은 <em>timesteps</em>와 <em>samples</em> 모두에 걸쳐 전이된다; clean time 근처에서 학습된 동일한 고정 steering vector는 intermediate noise level에서 각 generation trajectory에 주입되어도 여전히 효과적이며, 효율성을 유지하면서 정교한 conditional control을 제공한다. CIFAR-10, ImageNet, CelebA에서의 실험은 gradient-based guidance 대비 더 나은 accuracy/quality를 보이는 동시에, 상당한 inference speedup을 달성함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"64970","en":"Latent Diffusion Controller: Framework, Algorithms and Parameterization","ko":"Latent Diffusion Controller: 프레임워크, 알고리즘 및 매개변수화","authors":"Tong Yang, Moonkyung Ryu, Chih-wei Hsu, Guy Tennenholtz, Yuejie Chi, Craig Boutilier, Bo Dai","pos":"#2613","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=IGTMjtehxq","abs":"Controllable diffusion generation often relies on various heuristics that are seemingly disconnected without a unified understanding. We bridge this gap with Diffusion Controller (DiffCon), a unified control-theoretic view that casts reverse diffusion sampling as state-only stochastic control within (generalized) linearly-solvable Markov Decision Processes (LS-MDPs). Under this framework, control acts by reweighting the pretrained reverse-time transition kernels, balancing terminal objectives against an $f$-divergence cost. From the resulting optimality conditions, we derive practical reinforcement learning methods for diffusion fine-tuning: (i) $f$-divergence-regularized policy-gradient updates, including a PPO-style rule, and (ii) a regularizer-determined reward-weighted regression objective with a minimizer-preservation guarantee under the Kullback–Leibler (KL) divergence. The LS-MDP framework further implies a principled model form: the optimal score decomposes into a fixed pretrained baseline plus a lightweight control correction, motivating a side-network parameterization conditioned on exposed intermediate denoising outputs, enabling effective \\emph{gray-box adaptation} with a frozen backbone. Experiments on Stable Diffusion v1.4 across supervised and reward-driven finetuning show consistent gains in preference-alignment win rates and improved quality–efficiency trade-offs versus gray-box baselines and even the parameter-efficient white-box adapter LoRA."},{"id":"62638","en":"Latent-Guided Cooperative Energy-Based Models","ko":"잠재 유도 협력적 에너지 기반 모델","authors":"Cong Geng, Xue Han, Ye Yuan, Qiang Hu, Xin Huang, Ruiqiao Bai, JUNLAN FENG","pos":"#2614","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=emLXsVkbag","abs":"<p>Energy-based models (EBMs) provide a flexible framework for generative models with strong distribution modeling capabilities. Nevertheless, their broader adoption has been limited by the difficulty of stable and efficient training.  In this paper, we propose a unified and efficient latent-guided cooperative EBM that leverages informative target latent variables to guide the joint energy in capturing both data distribution and semantic structure, along with a cooperative generator designed for effective MCMC initialization. Our joint space optimization only requires MCMC sampling in the data space, and allows the energy to learn semantic data–latent relationships directly from real data.  Experiments show our method improves generation quality and training stability with fewer resources, and performs effectively across multiple downstream tasks.</p>","absKo":"<p>Energy-based model (EBM)은 강력한 distribution modeling 능력을 갖춘 generative model을 위한 유연한 framework를 제공한다. 그럼에도 불구하고, stable하고 efficient한 training의 어려움 때문에 보다 넓은 채택은 제한되어 왔다. 본 논문에서는 informative target latent variable을 활용해 joint energy가 data distribution과 semantic structure를 모두 포착하도록 유도하고, 효과적인 MCMC initialization을 위해 cooperative generator를 함께 설계한 unified하고 efficient한 latent-guided cooperative EBM을 제안한다. 우리의 joint space optimization은 data space에서의 MCMC sampling만을 필요로 하며, energy가 real data로부터 semantic data–latent relationship를 직접 학습할 수 있게 한다. 실험 결과, 우리의 방법은 더 적은 자원으로 generation quality와 training stability를 향상시키며, 여러 downstream task 전반에서 효과적으로 동작함을 보였다.</p>"},{"id":"64380","en":"Logical Guidance for the Exact Composition of Diffusion Models","ko":"Diffusion 모델의 정확한 합성을 위한 논리적 유도","authors":"Francesco Alesiani, Jonathan Warrell, Tanja Bien, Henrik Christiansen, Matheus Vitor Ferreira Ferraz, Mathias Niepert","pos":"#2615","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=OAM1jJsMGp","abs":"<p>We propose LOGDIFF (Logical Guidance for the Exact Composition of Diffusion Models), a guidance framework for diffusion models that enables principled constrained generation with complex logical expressions at inference time. We study when exact score-based guidance for complex logical formulas can be obtained from guidance signals associated with atomic attributes and constraints.   First, we derive an exact Boolean calculus that provides a sufficient condition for exact logical guidance. Specifically, if a formula admits a circuit representation in which conjunctions combine conditionally independent subformulas and disjunctions combine subformulas that are either conditionally independent or mutually exclusive, exact logical guidance is achievable. In this case, the guidance signal can be computed exactly from atomic scores and posterior probabilities using an efficient recursive algorithm. Moreover, we show that, for commonly encountered classes of distributions, any desired Boolean formula is compilable into such a circuit representation.   Second, by combining atomic guidance scores with posterior probability estimates, we introduce a hybrid guidance approach that bridges classifierguidance and classifier-free guidance, applicable to both compositional logical guidance and standard conditional generation.   We demonstrate the effectiveness of our framework on multiple image and protein structure generation tasks.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 LOGDIFF(Logical Guidance for the Exact Composition of Diffusion Models)를 제안한다. 이는 diffusion model을 위한 guidance framework로, inference time에 복잡한 logical expression에 대해 원칙적인 constrained generation을 가능하게 한다. 우리는 atomic attribute와 constraint에 연관된 guidance signal로부터 복잡한 logical formula에 대한 exact score-based guidance를 얻을 수 있는 조건을 연구한다.  먼저, exact logical guidance를 위한 충분 조건을 제공하는 정확한 Boolean calculus를 유도한다. 구체적으로, 어떤 formula가 conjunction이 conditionally independent한 subformula를 결합하고, disjunction이 conditionally independent하거나 mutually exclusive한 subformula를 결합하는 circuit representation을 허용한다면, exact logical guidance가 가능하다. 이 경우 guidance signal은 효율적인 recursive algorithm을 통해 atomic score와 posterior probability로부터 정확히 계산될 수 있다. 더 나아가, 흔히 접하는 distribution class에 대해서는 원하는 어떤 Boolean formula도 이러한 circuit representation으로 compilable함을 보인다.  둘째, atomic guidance score와 posterior probability estimate를 결합하여 classifier-guidance와 classifier-free guidance를 잇는 hybrid guidance approach를 제안하며, 이는 compositional logical guidance와 standard conditional generation 모두에 적용 가능하다.  우리는 여러 image 및 protein structure generation task에서 본 framework의 효과를 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"64440","en":"Calibrated Test-Time Guidance for Bayesian Inference","ko":"베이지안 추론을 위한 보정된 테스트 시점 유도","authors":"Daniel Geyfman, Felix Draxler, Jan Groeneveld, Hyunsoo Lee, Theofanis Karaletsos, Stephan Mandt","pos":"#2701","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=NZvWGf2XXM","abs":"<p>Test-time guidance is a widely used mechanism for steering pre-trained diffusion models toward outcomes specified by a reward function. Existing approaches, however, focus on reward maximization rather than sampling from the true Bayesian posterior, leading to miscalibrated inference. In this work, we show that common test-time guidance methods do not recover the correct posterior distribution and identify the structural approximations responsible for this failure. We then propose consistent alternative estimators that enable calibrated sampling from the Bayesian posterior. Across Bayesian inference and inverse problems, our approach yields substantially improved posterior calibration.</p>","absKo":"<p>Test-time guidance는 pre-trained diffusion model을 reward function이 지정한 결과로 유도하는 데 널리 사용되는 메커니즘이다. 그러나 기존 접근법은 true Bayesian posterior에서 샘플링하는 것보다 reward maximization에 초점을 맞추므로, calibration이 맞지 않는 inference를 초래한다. 이 연구에서 우리는 일반적인 test-time guidance 방법이 올바른 posterior distribution을 복원하지 못함을 보이고, 이러한 실패를 일으키는 구조적 approximation을 규명한다. 그런 다음 calibrated sampling이 가능한 consistent alternative estimator를 제안한다. Bayesian inference와 inverse problem 전반에 걸쳐, 우리의 접근법은 posterior calibration을 현저히 향상시킨다.</p>"},{"id":"62624","en":"Breaking the Factorization Barrier in Diffusion Language Models","ko":"Diffusion Language Models에서 Factorization Barrier 돌파","authors":"Ian Li, Zilei Shao, Benjie Wang, Rose Yu, Guy Van den Broeck, Anji Liu","pos":"#3510","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=euv8IoKFbh","abs":"<p>Diffusion language models theoretically allow for efficient parallel generation but are practically hindered by the \"factorization barrier\": the assumption that simultaneously predicted tokens are independent. This limitation forces a trade-off: models must either sacrifice speed by resolving dependencies sequentially or suffer from incoherence due to factorization. We argue that this barrier arises not from limited backbone expressivity, but from a structural misspecification: models are restricted to fully factorized outputs because explicitly parameterizing a joint distribution would require the Transformer to output a prohibitively large number of parameters. We propose <strong>Co</strong>upled <strong>D</strong>iscrete <strong>D</strong>iffusion (<strong>CoDD</strong>), a hybrid framework that breaks this barrier by replacing the fully-factorized output distribution with a lightweight, tractable probabilistic inference layer. This formulation yields a distribution family that is significantly more expressive than standard factorized priors, enabling the modeling of complex joint dependencies, yet remains compact enough to avoid the prohibitive parameter explosion associated with full joint modeling. Empirically, <strong>CoDD</strong> seamlessly enhances diverse diffusion language model architectures with negligible overhead, matching the reasoning performance of computationally intensive Reinforcement Learning baselines at a fraction of the training cost. Furthermore, it prevents performance collapse in few-step generation, enabling high-quality outputs at significantly reduced latencies.</p>","absKo":"Diffusion language model은 이론적으로 효율적인 병렬 생성을 가능하게 하지만, 실제로는 \"factorization barrier\"에 의해 제약됩니다. 즉, 동시에 예측된 token들이 서로 독립적이라고 가정하는 것입니다. 이 한계는 trade-off를 강요합니다. model은 dependency를 순차적으로 해소하면서 속도를 희생하거나, factorization 때문에 incoherence를 겪어야 합니다. 우리는 이 장벽이 backbone expressivity의 부족에서 비롯된 것이 아니라 structural misspecification에서 비롯된 것이라고 주장합니다. 명시적으로 joint distribution을 parameterize하려면 Transformer가 지나치게 많은 parameter를 출력해야 하므로, model은 fully factorized output으로 제한됩니다. 우리는 \\emph{Co}upled \\emph{D}iscrete \\emph{D}iffusion(\\emph{CoDD})을 제안합니다. 이는 fully-factorized output distribution을 가볍고 tractable한 probabilistic inference layer로 대체함으로써 이 장벽을 깨는 hybrid framework입니다. 이 formulation은 standard factorized prior보다 훨씬 더 expressive한 distribution family를 제공하여 복잡한 joint dependency를 모델링할 수 있게 하면서도, 전체 joint modeling에 수반되는 과도한 parameter explosion을 피할 만큼 compact합니다. 실험적으로, \\emph{CoDD}는 거의 overhead 없이 다양한 diffusion language model architecture를 자연스럽게 강화하며, 계산 집약적인 Reinforcement Learning baseline과 비견되는 reasoning performance를 훨씬 낮은 training cost로 달성합니다. 더 나아가 few-step generation에서의 성능 붕괴를 방지하여, 훨씬 낮은 latency로 고품질 output을 가능하게 합니다.</p>"},{"id":"63448","en":"Lookahead Path Likelihood Optimization for Diffusion LLMs","ko":"Diffusion LLM을 위한 룩어헤드 경로 우도 최적화","authors":"Xuejie Liu, Vit Chun Yap, Yitao Liang, Anji Liu","pos":"#3909","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=X8jXqDDaOT","abs":"<p>Diffusion Large Language Models (dLLMs) support arbitrary-order generation, yet their inference performance critically depends on the unmasking order. Existing strategies rely on heuristics that greedily optimize local confidence, offering limited guidance for identifying unmasking paths that are globally consistent and accurate. To bridge this gap, we introduce path log-likelihood (Path LL), a trajectory-conditioned objective that strongly correlates with downstream accuracy and enables principled selection of unmasking paths. To optimize Path LL at inference time, we propose POKE, an efficient value estimator that predicts the expected future Path LL of a partial decoding trajectory. We then integrate this lookahead signal into POKE-SMC, a Sequential Monte Carlo-based search framework for dynamically identifying optimal unmasking paths. Extensive experiments across 6 reasoning tasks show that POKE-SMC consistently improves accuracy, achieving 2\\%--3\\% average gains over strong decoding-time scaling baselines at comparable inference overhead on LLaDA models and advancing the accuracy--compute Pareto frontier.</p>","absKo":"<p>Diffusion Large Language Models (dLLMs)는 arbitrary-order generation을 지원하지만, 추론 성능은 unmasking order에 결정적으로 의존한다. 기존 전략들은 local confidence를 탐욕적으로 최적화하는 heuristic에 의존하여, 전역적으로 일관되고 정확한 unmasking path를 식별하는 데 제한적인 지침만을 제공한다. 이 간극을 메우기 위해, 우리는 downstream accuracy와 강하게 상관되며, unmasking path의 원리적 선택을 가능하게 하는 trajectory-conditioned objective인 path log-likelihood (Path LL)를 도입한다. 추론 시점에서 Path LL을 최적화하기 위해, 우리는 부분 decoding trajectory의 기대되는 미래 Path LL을 예측하는 효율적인 value estimator인 POKE를 제안한다. 그런 다음, 이 lookahead signal을 POKE-SMC에 통합하여, 최적의 unmasking path를 동적으로 식별하는 Sequential Monte Carlo 기반 search framework를 구성한다. 6개의 reasoning task에 걸친 광범위한 실험은 POKE-SMC가 일관되게 정확도를 향상시키며, LLaDA 모델에서 유사한 추론 오버헤드로 강력한 decoding-time scaling baseline 대비 평균 2\\%--3\\%의 성능 향상을 달성하고 accuracy--compute Pareto frontier를 전진시킴을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"65436","en":"Variational Entropic Optimal Transport","ko":"변분 엔트로피 Optimal Transport","authors":"Roman Dyachenko, Nikita Gushchin, Kirill Sokolov, Petr Mokrov, Evgeny Burnaev, Aleksandr Korotin","pos":"#4008","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=DgRd1uu8dj","abs":"Entropic optimal transport (EOT) in continuous spaces with quadratic cost is a classical tool for solving the domain translation problem. In practice, recent approaches optimize a weak dual EOT objective depending on a single potential, but doing so is computationally not efficient due to the intractable log-partition term. Existing methods typically resolve this obstacle in one of two ways: by significantly restricting the transport family to obtain closed-form normalization (via Gaussian-mixture parameterizations), or by using general neural parameterizations that require simulation-based training procedures. We propose Variational Entropic Optimal Transport (VarEOT), based on an exact variational reformulation of the log-partition $\\log \\mathbb{E}[\\exp(\\cdot)]$ as a tractable minimization over an auxiliary positive normalizer. This yields a differentiable learning objective optimized with stochastic gradients and avoids the necessity of MCMC simulations during the training. We provide theoretical guarantees, including finite-sample generalization bounds and approximation results under universal function approximation. Experiments on synthetic data and unpaired image-to-image translation demonstrate competitive or improved translation quality, while comparisons within the solvers that use the same weak dual EOT objective support the benefit of the proposed optimization principle."},{"id":"61293","en":"Distribution Matching Variational AutoEncoder","ko":"분포 정합 Variational AutoEncoder","authors":"Sen Ye, Jianning Pei, Mengde Xu, Shuyang Gu, Chunyu Wang, Liwei Wang, Han Hu","pos":"#208","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=re1J8BPwTQ","abs":"<p>Most visual generative models compress images into a latent space before applying diffusion or autoregressive modelling. Yet, existing approaches such as VAEs and foundation model aligned encoders implicitly constrain the latent space without explicitly shaping its distribution, making it unclear which types of distributions are optimal for modeling. We introduce <strong>Distribution-Matching VAE</strong> (<strong>DMVAE</strong>), which explicitly aligns the encoder’s latent distribution with an arbitrary reference distribution via a distribution matching constraint. This generalizes beyond the Gaussian prior of conventional VAEs, enabling alignment with distributions derived from self-supervised features, diffusion noise, or other prior distributions. With DMVAE, we can systematically investigate which latent distributions are more conducive to modeling, and we find that SSL-derived distributions provide an excellent balance between reconstruction fidelity and modeling efficiency, reaching a gFID of 3.2 on ImageNet with only 64 training epochs. Our results suggest that choosing a suitable latent distribution structure (achieved via distribution-level alignment), rather than relying on fixed priors, is key to bridging the gap between easy-to-model latents and high-fidelity image synthesis.</p>","absKo":"<p>대부분의 visual generative model은 diffusion 또는 autoregressive modeling을 적용하기 전에 이미지를 latent space로 압축한다. 그러나 VAE나 foundation model aligned encoder 같은 기존 접근은 latent space를 암묵적으로 제약하지만 그 분포를 명시적으로 형성하지 않기 때문에, 어떤 종류의 분포가 modeling에 최적인지 불분명하다. 우리는 encoder의 latent distribution을 임의의 reference distribution과 distribution matching constraint를 통해 명시적으로 정렬하는 <strong>Distribution-Matching VAE</strong> (<strong>DMVAE</strong>)를 제안한다. 이는 기존 VAE의 Gaussian prior를 넘어 self-supervised feature, diffusion noise, 또는 다른 prior distribution에서 유도된 분포와의 정렬을 가능하게 한다. DMVAE를 통해 우리는 어떤 latent distribution이 modeling에 더 적합한지 체계적으로 조사할 수 있으며, SSL에서 유도된 분포가 reconstruction fidelity와 modeling efficiency 사이에서 매우 우수한 균형을 제공하여, ImageNet에서 단 64 epoch의 training으로 gFID 3.2를 달성함을 발견했다. 우리의 결과는 고정된 prior에 의존하기보다, distribution-level alignment를 통해 달성되는 적절한 latent distribution structure를 선택하는 것이 쉽게 모델링 가능한 latent와 고충실도 image synthesis 사이의 간극을 메우는 핵심임을 시사한다.</p>"},{"id":"65510","en":"Trajectory Consistency for One-Step Generation on Euler Mean Flows","ko":"Euler Mean Flow에서 One-Step 생성을 위한 궤적 일관성","authors":"Zhiqi Li, Yuchen Sun, Duowen Chen, Jinjin He, Bo Zhu","pos":"#2401","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=CuqZJO3RE4","abs":"We propose \\emph{Euler Mean Flows (EMF)}, a flow-based generative framework for one-step and few-step generation that enforces long-range trajectory consistency with minimal sampling cost.  The key idea of EMF is to replace the trajectory consistency constraint, which is difficult to supervise and optimize over long time scales, with a principled linear surrogate that enables direct data supervision for long-horizon flow-map compositions.  We derive this approximation from the semigroup formulation of flow-based models and show that, under mild regularity assumptions, it faithfully approximates the original consistency objective while being substantially easier to optimize.  This formulation leads to a unified, JVP-free training framework that supports both $u$-prediction and $x_1$-prediction variants, avoiding explicit Jacobian computations and significantly reducing memory and computational overhead.  Experiments on image synthesis, particle-based geometry generation, and functional generation demonstrate improved optimization stability and sample quality under fixed sampling budgets, together with approximately $50\\%$ reductions in training time and memory consumption compared to existing one-step methods for image generation."},{"id":"66622","en":"Stronger Semantic Encoders Can Harm Relighting Performance: A Probe of Visual Priors via Augmented Latent Intrinsics","ko":"더 강한 의미 인코더가 Relighting 성능을 해칠 수 있다: 증강 잠재 고유값을 통한 시각 사전 지식 탐침","authors":"Xiaoyan Xing, Xiao Zhang, Sezer Karaoglu, Theo Gevers, Anand Bhattad","pos":"#2501","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=23pS2aZozA","abs":"<p>Image-to-image relighting requires representations that disentangle scene properties from illumination. Recent methods rely on latent intrinsic representations but remain under-constrained and often fail on challenging materials such as metal and glass. A natural hypothesis is that stronger pretrained visual priors should resolve these failures. We find the opposite: features from top-performing semantic encoders often degrade relighting quality, revealing a fundamental trade-off between semantic abstraction and photometric fidelity. We study this trade-off and introduce Augmented Latent Intrinsics (ALI), which balances semantic context and dense photometric structure by fusing features from a pixel-aligned visual encoder into a latent-intrinsic framework, together with a self-supervised refinement strategy to mitigate the scarcity of paired real-world data. Trained only on unlabeled real-world image pairs and paired with a dense, pixel-aligned visual prior, ALI achieves strong relighting improvements, with the largest gains on complex, specular materials.</p>"},{"id":"61152","en":"Spectral Evolution Search: Efficient Inference-Time Scaling for Reward-Aligned Image Generation","ko":"Spectral Evolution Search: Reward-Aligned Image Generation을 위한 효율적 Inference-Time Scaling","authors":"Jinyan Ye, Zhongjie Duan, Zhiwen Li, Cen Chen, Daoyuan Chen, Yaliang Li, Yingda Chen","pos":"#2504","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=tBt12b9dxa","abs":"<p>Inference-time scaling offers a versatile paradigm for aligning visual generative models with downstream objectives without parameter updates. However, existing approaches that optimize the high-dimensional initial noise suffer from severe inefficiency, as many search directions exert negligible influence on the final generation. We show that this inefficiency is closely related to a spectral bias in generative dynamics: model sensitivity to initial perturbations diminishes rapidly as frequency increases. Building on this insight, we propose Spectral Evolution Search (SES), a plug-and-play framework for initial noise optimization that executes gradient-free evolutionary search within a low-frequency subspace. Theoretically, we derive the Spectral Scaling Prediction from perturbation propagation dynamics, which explains the systematic differences in the impact of perturbations across frequencies. Extensive experiments demonstrate that SES significantly advances the Pareto frontier of generation quality versus computational cost, consistently outperforming strong baselines under equivalent budgets. Our code is available at \\url{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/Spectral-Evolution-Search-66DB}.</p>","absKo":"Inference-time scaling은 parameter update 없이 downstream objective에 visual generative model을 정렬하는 다재다능한 paradigm을 제공한다. 그러나 고차원 initial noise를 최적화하는 기존 접근법은 심각한 비효율을 겪는데, 이는 많은 search direction이 최종 생성에 거의 영향을 미치지 않기 때문이다. 우리는 이러한 비효율이 generative dynamics의 spectral bias와 밀접하게 관련되어 있음을 보인다. 즉, 초기 perturbation에 대한 model sensitivity는 frequency가 증가할수록 빠르게 감소한다. 이 통찰을 바탕으로, 우리는 저주파 subspace 내에서 gradient-free evolutionary search를 수행하는 initial noise optimization을 위한 plug-and-play framework인 Spectral Evolution Search(SES)를 제안한다. 이론적으로 우리는 perturbation propagation dynamics로부터 Spectral Scaling Prediction을 도출하며, 이는 frequency 전반에 걸친 perturbation 영향의 체계적 차이를 설명한다. 광범위한 실험은 SES가 generation quality와 computational cost 간 Pareto frontier를 크게 진전시키며, 동일한 budget에서 강력한 baseline을 일관되게 능가함을 보여준다. 우리의 코드는 \\url{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/Spectral-Evolution-Search-66DB}에서 확인할 수 있다.</p>"},{"id":"65611","en":"Riemannian MeanFlow","ko":"리만 MeanFlow","authors":"Dongyeop Woo, Marta Skreta, Seonghyun Park, Kirill Neklyudov, Sungsoo Ahn","pos":"#2507","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=BvWEy6Pznz","abs":"Diffusion and flow models have become the dominant paradigm for generative modeling on Riemannian manifolds, with successful applications in protein backbone generation and DNA sequence design. However, these methods require tens to hundreds of neural network evaluations at inference time, which can become a computational bottleneck in large-scale scientific sampling workflows. We introduce Riemannian MeanFlow (RMF), a framework for learning flow maps directly on manifolds, enabling high-quality generations with as few as one forward pass. We derive three equivalent characterizations of the manifold average velocity (Eulerian, Lagrangian, and semigroup identities), and analyze parameterizations and stabilization techniques to improve training on high-dimensional manifolds. In promoter DNA design and protein backbone generation settings, RMF achieves comparable sample quality to prior methods while requiring up to 10$\\times$ fewer function evaluations. Finally, we show that few-step flow maps enable efficient reward-guided design through reward look-ahead, where terminal states can be predicted from intermediate steps at minimal additional cost."},{"id":"63515","en":"One-step Latent-free Image Generation with Pixel Mean Flows","ko":"Pixel Mean Flow를 활용한 원스텝 잠재 프리 이미지 생성","authors":"Yiyang Lu, Susie Lu, Qiao Sun, Hanhong Zhao, Zhicheng Jiang, Xianbang Wang, Tianhong Li, Zhengyang Geng, Kaiming He","pos":"#2513","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=WUK8JIeetF","abs":"Modern diffusion/flow-based models for image generation typically exhibit two core characteristics: (i) using multi-step sampling, and (ii) operating in a latent space. Recent advances have made encouraging progress on each aspect individually, paving the way toward one-step diffusion/flow without latents. In this work, we take a further step towards this goal and propose \"pixel MeanFlow\" (pMF). Our core guideline is to formulate the network output space and the loss space separately. The network target is designed to be on a presumed low-dimensional image manifold (i.e., x-prediction), while the loss is defined via MeanFlow in the velocity space. We introduce a simple transformation between the image manifold and the average velocity field. In experiments, pMF achieves strong results for one-step latent-free generation on ImageNet at 256$\\times$256 resolution (2.22 FID) and 512$\\times$512 resolution (2.48 FID), filling a key missing piece in this regime. We hope that our study will further advance the boundaries of diffusion/flow-based generative models.","absKo":"이미지 생성을 위한 현대 diffusion/flow-based model은 일반적으로 두 가지 핵심 특성을 보인다. (i) multi-step sampling을 사용하고, (ii) latent space에서 동작한다는 점이다. 최근의 진전은 각 측면에서 개별적으로 고무적인 성과를 내며, latent 없이 one-step diffusion/flow로 나아갈 길을 열었다. 본 연구에서는 이 목표를 향한 한 걸음을 더 내딛어 \"pixel MeanFlow\"(pMF)를 제안한다. 우리의 핵심 원칙은 network output space와 loss space를 분리하여 정식화하는 것이다. network target은 저차원 image manifold라고 가정되는 공간(즉, x-prediction) 위에 있도록 설계하고, loss는 velocity space에서 MeanFlow를 통해 정의한다. 우리는 image manifold와 average velocity field 사이의 간단한 변환을 도입한다. 실험에서 pMF는 ImageNet 256$\\times$256 해상도(2.22 FID)와 512$\\times$512 해상도(2.48 FID)에서 latent-free one-step generation을 위한 강력한 결과를 달성하며, 이 영역에서 중요한 공백을 메운다. 우리의 연구가 diffusion/flow-based generative model의 경계를 더 확장하길 기대한다.</p>"},{"id":"68833","en":"Designing a Conditional Prior Distribution for Flow-Based Generative Models","ko":"Flow 기반 Generative Model을 위한 조건부 사전 분포 설계","authors":"Noam Issachar, Mohammad Salama, Raanan Fattal, Sagie Benaim","pos":"#2601","abs":"<p>Flow-based generative models have recently shown impressive performance for conditional generation tasks, such as text-to-image generation. However, current methods transform a general unimodal noise distribution to a specific mode of the target data distribution. As such, every point in the initial source distribution can be mapped to every point in the target distribution, resulting in long average paths. To this end, in this work, we tap into a non-utilized property of conditional flow-based models: the ability to design a non-trivial prior distribution. Given an input condition, such as a text prompt, we first map it to a point lying in data space, representing an “average\" data point with the minimal average distance to all data points of the same conditional mode (e.g., class). We then utilize the flow matching formulation to map samples from a parametric distribution centered around this point to the conditional target distribution. Experimentally, our method significantly improves training times and generation efficiency (FID, KID and CLIP alignment scores) compared to baselines, producing high quality samples using fewer sampling steps. Code is available at https://github.com/MoSalama98/conditional-prior-flow-matching.</p>"},{"id":"66686","en":"DirectEdit: Step-Level Accurate Inversion for Flow-Based Image Editing","ko":"DirectEdit: Flow 기반 이미지 편집을 위한 Step-Level 정확 역변환","authors":"Desong Yang, Mang Ye","pos":"#2603","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=1MT6RdvOcT","abs":"<p>With recent advancements in large-scale pre-trained text-to-image (T2I) models, training-free image editing methods have demonstrated remarkable success. Typically, these methods involve adding noise to a clean image via an inversion process, followed by separate denoising steps for the reconstruction and editing paths during the forward process. However, since the reconstruction path is approximated using noisy latents from mismatched timesteps, existing methods inevitably suffer from accumulated drift, which fundamentally limits reconstruction fidelity. To address this challenge, we systematically analyze the inversion process within the flow transformer and propose DirectEdit, a simple yet efficient editing method that eliminates the inherent reconstruction error without introducing additional neural function evaluations (NFEs). Unlike most prior works that attempt to rectify the inversion path, DirectEdit focuses on directly aligning the forward paths, enabling precise reconstruction and reliable feature sharing. Furthermore, we introduce a preservation mechanism based on attention feature injection and multi-branch mask-guided noise blending, which effectively balances fidelity and editability. Extensive experiments across diverse scenarios demonstrate that DirectEdit achieves efficient and accurate image editing, delivering superior performance that outperforms state-of-the-art methods. Code will be released.</p>"},{"id":"62568","en":"End-to-End Autoregressive Image Generation with 1D Semantic Tokenizer","ko":"1D Semantic Tokenizer를 활용한 End-to-End Autoregressive Image Generation","authors":"Wenda Chu, Bingliang Zhang, Jiaqi Han, Yizhuo Li, Linjie Yang, Yisong Yue, Qiushan Guo","pos":"#2605","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=fSnxuRhWoC","abs":"<p>Autoregressive image modeling relies on visual tokenizers to compress images into compact latent representations. We design an end-to-end training pipeline that jointly optimizes reconstruction and generation, enabling direct supervision from generation results to the tokenizer. This contrasts with prior two-stage approaches that train tokenizers and generative models separately. We further investigate leveraging vision foundation models to improve 1D tokenizers for autoregressive modeling. Our autoregressive generative model achieves strong empirical results, including a state-of-the-art FID score of 1.48 without guidance on ImageNet 256×256 generation.</p>","absKo":"<p>Autoregressive image modeling은 이미지를 압축된 latent representation으로 압축하기 위해 visual tokenizer에 의존한다. 우리는 reconstruction과 generation을 공동으로 최적화하는 end-to-end training pipeline을 설계하여, generation 결과로부터 tokenizer에 직접 supervision이 가능하게 한다. 이는 tokenizer와 generative model을 분리해 학습하는 기존의 two-stage 접근과 대조된다. 또한 autoregressive modeling을 위한 1D tokenizer를 개선하기 위해 vision foundation model을 활용하는 방법도 추가로 조사한다. 우리의 autoregressive generative model은 ImageNet 256×256 generation에서 guidance 없이도 state-of-the-art FID 점수 1.48을 포함한 강력한 실증 결과를 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"64277","en":"Flash-VAED: Plug-and-Play VAE Decoders for Efficient Video Generation","ko":"Flash-VAED: 효율적 영상 생성을 위한 플러그 앤 플레이 VAE 디코더","authors":"Lunjie Zhu, Yushi Huang, Xingtong Ge, Yufei Xue, Zhening Liu, Yumeng Zhang, Zehong Lin, Jun Zhang","pos":"#2608","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=PDBLtVDb0d","abs":"Latent diffusion models have enabled high-quality video synthesis, yet their inference remains costly and time-consuming. As diffusion transformers become increasingly efficient, the latency bottleneck inevitably shifts to VAE decoders. To reduce their latency while maintaining quality, we propose a universal acceleration framework for VAE decoders that preserves full alignment with the original latent distribution. Specifically, we propose (1) an *independence-aware channel pruning* method to effectively mitigate severe channel redundancy, and (2) a *stage-wise dominant operator optimization* strategy to address the high inference cost of the widely used causal 3D convolutions in VAE decoders. Based on these innovations, we construct a **Flash-VAED** family. Moreover, we design a *three-phase dynamic distillation* framework that efficiently transfers the capabilities of the original VAE decoder to Flash-VAED. Extensive experiments on Wan and LTX-Video VAE decoders demonstrate that our method outperforms baselines in both quality and speed, achieving approximately a **6$\\times$ speedup** while maintaining the reconstruction performance up to **96.9%**. Notably, Flash-VAED accelerates the end-to-end generation pipeline by up to **36%** with negligible quality drops on VBench-2.0.","absKo":"Latent diffusion model은 고품질 video synthesis를 가능하게 했지만, inference는 여전히 비용이 크고 시간이 많이 든다. diffusion transformer가 점점 더 효율적으로 변함에 따라 latency bottleneck은 불가피하게 VAE decoder로 이동한다. 품질을 유지하면서 latency를 줄이기 위해, 우리는 원래 latent distribution과의 완전한 alignment를 보존하는 VAE decoder용 범용 가속 framework를 제안한다. 구체적으로, 우리는 (1) 심각한 channel redundancy를 효과적으로 완화하는 *independence-aware channel pruning* 방법과, (2) VAE decoder에서 널리 사용되는 causal 3D convolution의 높은 inference cost를 해결하는 *stage-wise dominant operator optimization* 전략을 제안한다. 이러한 혁신을 바탕으로 우리는 **Flash-VAED** family를 구축한다. 또한, 원래 VAE decoder의 능력을 Flash-VAED로 효율적으로 이전하는 *three-phase dynamic distillation* framework를 설계한다. Wan 및 LTX-Video VAE decoder에 대한 광범위한 실험은 우리의 방법이 품질과 속도 모두에서 baseline을 능가함을 보여주며, reconstruction performance의 최대 **96.9%**를 유지하면서 약 **6$\\times$ speedup**을 달성한다. 특히 Flash-VAED는 VBench-2.0에서 품질 저하가 거의 없이 end-to-end generation pipeline을 최대 **36%**까지 가속한다."},{"id":"65212","en":"LUVE : Latent-Cascaded Ultra-High-Resolution Video Generation with Dual Frequency Experts","ko":"LUVE: Dual Frequency Expert를 이용한 잠재 캐스케이드 초고해상도 비디오 생성","authors":"Chen Zhao, Jiawei Chen, Hongyu Li, Zhuoliang Kang, Shilin Lu, Xiaoming Wei, Kai Zhang, Jian Yang, Ying Tai","pos":"#2611","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=FjZF2l8ZZF","abs":"<p>Recent advances in video diffusion models have significantly improved visual quality, yet ultra-high-resolution (UHR) video generation remains a formidable challenge due to the compounded difficulties of motion modeling, semantic planning, and detail synthesis. To address these limitations, we propose \\textbf{LUVE}, a \\textbf{L}atent-cascaded \\textbf{U}HR \\textbf{V}ideo generation framework built upon dual frequency \\textbf{E}xperts. LUVE employs a three-stage architecture comprising low-resolution motion generation for motion-consistent latent synthesis, video latent upsampling that performs resolution upsampling directly in the latent space to mitigate memory and computational overhead, and high-resolution content refinement that integrates low-frequency and high-frequency experts to jointly enhance semantic coherence and fine-grained detail generation. Extensive experiments demonstrate that our LUVE achieves superior photorealism and content fidelity in UHR video generation, and comprehensive ablation studies further validate the effectiveness of each component.</p>"},{"id":"61255","en":"Concept Removal for Frontier Image Generative Models","ko":"Frontier Image Generative Model을 위한 Concept Removal","authors":"Pierre Joly, Aditya Kumar, Adam Dziedzic, Franziska Boenisch","pos":"#2700","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=s7NR3XGdwq","abs":"<p>Image generative models are trained on massive, largely uncurated internet-scale datasets that contain undesirable visual concepts. Efficiently removing such concepts from the model generations without degrading the quality of output images remains challenging. We introduce a novel concept removal method for frontier diffusion and image autoregressive models, such as, SD3.5, Flux, and Infinity. Our intervention replaces the internal bottleneck layer present in all these modern models with a transcoder that is trained to replicate the original layer while structuring it into distinct activation features. This in‑place substitution creates an integrated filter through which concept‑specific signals can be selectively disabled while preserving the rest of the model’s behavior. Since the intervention modifies the model backbone rather than attaching an external component, it remains persistent under white‑box access. Empirically, the approach achieves state‑of‑the‑art concept removal performance across modern diffusion and autoregressive models, maintains visual generation quality, provides robustness against adversarial prompts, and supports sequential removal of diverse concepts. This positions our method as a practical approach for concept removal in frontier image generative models.</p>","absKo":"<p>이미지 generative model은 바람직하지 않은 visual concept을 포함하는 거대하고 대체로 비선별적인 internet-scale dataset으로 학습된다. 출력 이미지의 품질을 저하시키지 않으면서 이러한 concept을 model generation에서 효율적으로 제거하는 것은 여전히 어렵다. 우리는 SD3.5, Flux, Infinity와 같은 frontier diffusion 및 image autoregressive model을 위한 새로운 concept removal method를 제안한다. 우리의 개입은 이들 모든 현대적 model에 공통적으로 존재하는 internal bottleneck layer를, 원래 layer를 그대로 복제하면서도 이를 서로 구분되는 activation feature로 구조화하도록 학습된 transcoder로 교체한다. 이 in-place substitution은 model의 나머지 동작은 보존하면서 concept-specific signal을 선택적으로 비활성화할 수 있는 통합 filter를 만든다. 이 개입은 외부 component를 부착하는 것이 아니라 model backbone 자체를 수정하므로, white-box access 하에서도 지속성을 유지한다. 실험적으로, 이 접근법은 현대 diffusion 및 autoregressive model 전반에서 state-of-the-art concept removal 성능을 달성하고, visual generation quality를 유지하며, adversarial prompt에 대한 robustness를 제공하고, 다양한 concept의 순차적 제거를 지원한다. 이는 우리 방법을 frontier image generative model에서 concept removal을 위한 실용적 접근법으로 자리매김하게 한다.</p>"},{"id":"64038","en":"A Diffusive Classification Loss for Learning Energy-based Generative Models","ko":"에너지 기반 생성 모델 학습을 위한 확산형 분류 손실","authors":"RuiKang OuYang, Louis Grenioux, Jose Miguel Hernandez-Lobato","pos":"#2703","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=RVPqygyGRu","abs":"<p>Score-based generative models have recently achieved remarkable success. While they are usually parameterized by the score, an alternative way is to use a series of time-dependent energy-based models (EBMs), where the score is obtained from the negative input-gradient of the energy. Crucially, EBMs can be leveraged not only for generation, but also for tasks such as compositional sampling or building Boltzmann Generators via Monte Carlo methods. However, training EBMs remains challenging. Direct maximum likelihood is computationally prohibitive due to the need for nested sampling, while score matching, though efficient, suffers from mode blindness. To address these issues, we introduce the Diffusive Classification (DiffCLF) objective, a simple method that avoids blindness while remaining computationally efficient. DiffCLF reframes EBM learning as a supervised classification problem across noise levels, and can be seamlessly combined with standard score-based objectives. We validate the effectiveness of DiffCLF by comparing the estimated energies against ground truth in analytical Gaussian mixture cases, and by applying the trained models to tasks such as model composition and Boltzmann Generator sampling. Our results show that DiffCLF enables EBMs with higher fidelity and broader applicability than existing approaches.</p>","absKo":"<p>Score-based generative model은 최근 놀라운 성공을 거두었다. 이들은 보통 score로 parameterize되지만, 대안적으로는 일련의 time-dependent energy-based model (EBM)을 사용할 수 있으며, 이때 score는 energy의 음의 input-gradient로부터 얻어진다. 특히 EBM은 생성뿐 아니라 compositional sampling이나 Monte Carlo method를 통한 Boltzmann Generator 구축과 같은 작업에도 활용될 수 있다. 그러나 EBM의 학습은 여전히 어렵다. 직접적인 maximum likelihood는 nested sampling의 필요 때문에 계산적으로 비현실적이며, score matching은 효율적이지만 mode blindness 문제를 겪는다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 blindness를 피하면서도 계산적으로 효율적인 간단한 방법인 Diffusive Classification (DiffCLF) objective를 도입한다. DiffCLF는 EBM 학습을 noise level 전반의 supervised classification problem으로 재구성하며, 표준 score-based objective와도 매끄럽게 결합될 수 있다. 우리는 analytical Gaussian mixture case에서 추정된 energy를 ground truth와 비교하고, 학습된 model을 model composition 및 Boltzmann Generator sampling과 같은 task에 적용함으로써 DiffCLF의 효과를 검증한다. 결과는 DiffCLF가 기존 접근법보다 더 높은 fidelity와 더 넓은 applicability를 가진 EBM을 가능하게 함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"62032","en":"Mode Seeking meets Mean Seeking for Long Video Generation","ko":"긴 영상 생성에서 Mode Seeking과 Mean Seeking의 결합","authors":"Shengqu Cai, Weili Nie, Chao Liu, Julius Berner, Lvmin Zhang, Nanye Ma, Hansheng Chen, Maneesh Agrawala, Leonidas Guibas, Gordon Wetzstein, Arash Vahdat","pos":"#3407","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=kVBNDXHVeo","abs":"<p>Scaling video generation from seconds to minutes faces a critical bottleneck: while short-video data is abundant and high-fidelity, coherent long-form data is scarce and limited to narrow domains. While multi-resolution image training works because higher resolution is largely an interpolation of the same underlying patch distribution, training across video lengths is fundamentally different: a longer video is an extrapolation that must invent new events and causal structure beyond the short-clip horizon. To address this, we propose a training paradigm where Mode Seeking meets Mean Seeking, decoupling local fidelity from long-term coherence from a unified representation via a Decoupled Diffusion Transformer. Our approach utilizes a global Flow Matching head trained via supervised learning on long videos to capture narrative structure, while simultaneously employing a local Distribution Matching head that aligns sliding windows to a frozen short-video teacher via a mode-seeking reverse-KL divergence. This strategy enables the synthesis of minute-scale videos that learns long-range coherence and motions from limited long videos via supervised flow matching, while inheriting local realism by aligning every sliding-window segment of the student to a frozen short-video teacher.</p>","absKo":"<p>몇 초에서 몇 분으로 video generation을 확장하는 것은 중대한 병목에 직면한다. short-video data는 풍부하고 fidelity가 높지만, coherent한 long-form data는 희소하며 좁은 도메인에 제한되어 있다. multi-resolution image training이 잘 작동하는 이유는 더 높은 해상도가 본질적으로 동일한 underlying patch distribution의 interpolation이기 때문이지만, video length에 걸친 training은 근본적으로 다르다. 더 긴 video는 short-clip horizon을 넘어 새로운 사건과 causal structure를 만들어내야 하는 extrapolation이다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 Mode Seeking이 Mean Seeking과 만나는 training paradigm을 제안하며, Decoupled Diffusion Transformer를 통해 unified representation에서 local fidelity와 long-term coherence를 분리한다. 우리의 접근은 long video로 supervised learning을 통해 학습된 global Flow Matching head를 활용하여 narrative structure를 포착하는 동시에, mode-seeking reverse-KL divergence를 사용해 sliding window를 frozen short-video teacher에 정렬하는 local Distribution Matching head를 병행한다. 이 전략은 supervised flow matching을 통해 제한된 long video로부터 long-range coherence와 motion을 학습하는 동시에, student의 모든 sliding-window segment를 frozen short-video teacher에 정렬함으로써 local realism을 계승하여 minute-scale video의 합성을 가능하게 한다.</p>"},{"id":"61617","en":"Semantic Granularity Navigation in Image Editing","ko":"Image Editing에서 Semantic Granularity Navigation","authors":"Liangsi Lu, Minzhe Guo, Xuhang Chen, Yang Shi","pos":"#803","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=oTRMveQEzW","abs":"<p>Despite the generative capabilities of diffusion models, real-image editing remains constrained by a persistent trade-off between semantic editability and structural fidelity. We identify a primary cause of this limitation as the implicit coupling of editing progress with noise scale in existing paradigms. This coupling creates a budget misallocation: achieving stronger semantic changes often necessitates initializing from high-noise states, which can consume computation on disrupting global layout before semantic modification begins. To address this, we introduce NaviEdit, a training-free framework that decouples the editing trajectory from the denoising schedule via a strict Time-Axis Consistency principle. By reformulating editing as controlled vector field navigation on a distinct task axis, NaviEdit strategically concentrates the computational budget within semantically responsive intermediate scales while reducing exposure to destructive high-noise regimes. Experiments show that NaviEdit outperforms strong state-of-the-art baselines across PIE-Bench, achieving larger semantic edits with better structure preservation under comparable compute budgets, without requiring model tuning.</p>","absKo":"<p>diffusion model의 생성 능력에도 불구하고, real-image editing은 semantic editability와 structural fidelity 사이의 지속적인 trade-off에 의해 제약을 받아왔다. 우리는 기존 패러다임에서 이 한계의 주된 원인을 editing progress와 noise scale의 암묵적 결합으로 파악한다. 이러한 결합은 budget misallocation을 초래하는데, 더 강한 semantic change를 달성하려면 종종 high-noise state에서 초기화해야 하며, 이로 인해 semantic modification이 시작되기 전에 전역 레이아웃을 교란하는 데 계산 자원이 소모된다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 엄격한 Time-Axis Consistency 원리를 통해 editing trajectory를 denoising schedule과 분리하는 training-free framework인 NaviEdit를 제안한다. editing을 별도의 task axis 위에서 제어된 vector field navigation으로 재정식화함으로써, NaviEdit는 semantically responsive한 중간 scale에 계산 budget을 전략적으로 집중시키면서 파괴적인 high-noise regime에 대한 노출을 줄인다. 실험 결과 NaviEdit는 model tuning 없이도, 비슷한 compute budget 하에서 구조 보존은 더 좋으면서 더 큰 semantic edit를 달성하여 PIE-Bench 전반의 강력한 state-of-the-art baseline을 능가함을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"62717","en":"Optimizing Visual Generative Models via Distribution-wise Rewards","ko":"분포 단위 보상으로 Visual Generative Models 최적화","authors":"Ruihang Li, Mengde Xu, Shuyang Gu, Leigang Qu, Fuli Feng, Han Hu, Wenjie Wang","pos":"#909","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=dxi8kGgKMM","abs":"<p>Conventional reinforcement learning strategies for visual generation typically employ sample-wise reward functions, yet this practice frequently results in reward hacking that degrades image diversity and introduces visual anomalies. To address these limitations, we present a novel framework that finetunes generative models using distribution-wise rewards, ensuring better alignment with real-world data distributions. Unlike rewards that evaluate samples individually, distribution-wise reward accounts for the data distribution of the samples, mitigating the mode collapse problem that occurs when all samples optimize towards the same direction independently. To overcome the prohibitive computational cost of estimating these rewards, we introduce a subset-replace strategy that efficiently provides reward signals by updating only a small subset of a generated reference set. Additionally, we apply RL to optimize post-hoc model merging coefficients, potentially mitigating the train-inference inconsistency caused by introducing stochastic differential equation (SDE) in regular RL practices. Extensive experiments show our approach significantly improves FID-50K across various base models, from 8.30 to 5.77 for SiT and from 3.74 to 3.52 for EDM2. Qualitative evaluation also confirms that our method enhances perceptual quality while preserving sample diversity.</p>","absKo":"<p>시각 생성에 대한 기존 reinforcement learning 전략은 일반적으로 sample-wise reward function을 사용하지만, 이러한 방식은 종종 reward hacking을 초래하여 image diversity를 저하시고 visual anomaly를 유발한다. 이러한 한계를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 distribution-wise reward를 사용하여 generative model을 fine-tune하는 새로운 framework를 제시하며, 이를 통해 실제 데이터 분포와의 정렬을 더 잘 보장한다. 개별 sample을 평가하는 reward와 달리, distribution-wise reward는 sample의 data distribution을 고려하므로, 모든 sample이 독립적으로 같은 방향으로 최적화될 때 발생하는 mode collapse 문제를 완화한다. 이러한 reward를 추정하는 데 드는 막대한 계산 비용을 극복하기 위해, 우리는 생성된 reference set의 작은 부분집합만 갱신하는 subset-replace strategy를 도입하여 효율적으로 reward signal을 제공한다. 추가로, 우리는 post-hoc model merging coefficient를 최적화하기 위해 RL을 적용하여, 일반적인 RL practice에서 stochastic differential equation(SDE)을 도입함으로써 발생할 수 있는 train-inference inconsistency를 완화할 가능성을 높인다. 광범위한 실험은 우리의 접근법이 다양한 base model에서 FID-50K를 크게 향상시킴을 보여주며, SiT에서는 8.30에서 5.77로, EDM2에서는 3.74에서 3.52로 개선되었다. 정성적 평가 또한 우리의 방법이 sample diversity를 보존하면서 perceptual quality를 향상시킴을 확인한다.</p>"},{"id":"60516","en":"MAMBO-G: Magnitude-Aware Mitigation for Boosted Guidance","ko":"MAMBO-G: Boosted Guidance를 위한 Magnitude-Aware Mitigation","authors":"Shangwen Zhu, Qianyu Peng, Zhilei Shu, Yuting Hu, Han Zhang, Andy Zheng, Xinyu Cui, Jian Zhao, Ruili Feng, Fan Cheng","pos":"#912","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=zSKSZm46DO","abs":"High-fidelity text-to-image and text-to-video generation typically relies on Classifier-Free Guidance (CFG), but achieving optimal results often demands computationally expensive sampling schedules. In this work, we propose MAMBO-G, a training-free acceleration framework that significantly reduces computational cost by dynamically optimizing guidance magnitudes. We observe that standard CFG schedules are inefficient, applying disproportionately large updates in early steps that hinder convergence speed. MAMBO-G mitigates this by modulating the guidance scale based on the update-to-prediction magnitude ratio, effectively stabilizing the trajectory and enabling rapid convergence. This efficiency is particularly vital for resource-intensive tasks like video generation. Our method serves as a universal plug-and-play accelerator, achieving up to 3$\\times$ speedup on Stable Diffusion v3.5 (SD3.5) and 4$\\times$ on Lumina. Most notably, MAMBO-G accelerates the 14B-parameter Wan2.1 video model by 2$\\times$ while preserving visual fidelity, offering a practical solution for efficient large-scale video synthesis. Our implementation follows a mainstream open-source diffusion framework and is plug-and-play with existing pipelines.","absKo":"고충실도 text-to-image 및 text-to-video 생성은 일반적으로 Classifier-Free Guidance (CFG)에 의존하지만, 최적의 결과를 얻으려면 계산 비용이 큰 sampling schedule이 필요한 경우가 많다. 본 연구에서는 guidance magnitude를 동적으로 최적화하여 계산 비용을 크게 줄이는 training-free 가속 프레임워크인 MAMBO-G를 제안한다. 우리는 표준 CFG schedule이 비효율적이며, 초반 단계에서 불균형적으로 큰 update를 적용해 수렴 속도를 저해한다는 점을 관찰했다. MAMBO-G는 update-to-prediction magnitude ratio를 바탕으로 guidance scale을 조절함으로써 이를 완화하고, trajectory를 효과적으로 안정화하며 빠른 수렴을 가능하게 한다. 이러한 효율성은 video generation 같은 자원 집약적 작업에서 특히 중요하다. 우리의 방법은 범용 plug-and-play accelerator로 작동하며, Stable Diffusion v3.5 (SD3.5)에서 최대 3$\\times$, Lumina에서 4$\\times$의 속도 향상을 달성한다. 특히 MAMBO-G는 14B-parameter Wan2.1 video model을 visual fidelity를 유지하면서 2$\\times$ 가속하여, 효율적인 대규모 video synthesis를 위한 실용적 해법을 제공한다. 구현은 주류 open-source diffusion framework를 따르며 기존 pipeline과 plug-and-play로 호환된다."},{"id":"63480","en":"LiteVSR: Enabling Cross-Domain Fine-Grained Detail Generation in Light-Weight Transformers for Video Super-Resolution","ko":"LiteVSR: 비디오 초해상도를 위한 경량 Transformer에서 교차 도메인 세밀 디테일 생성 구현","authors":"Yu Cao, Ziquan Liu, Zhensong Zhang, Jiankang Deng, Shaogang Gong, Jifei Song","pos":"#914","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=WqowD8RxEk","abs":"<p>Large-scale pre-trained video generators offer powerful priors for Video Super-Resolution (VSR), yet adapting them remains computationally prohibitive. Full fine-tuning demands extensive resources, and ControlNet-style adapters lose their efficiency advantage under modern Diffusion Transformers (DiTs) since the absence of encoder-decoder hierarchy forces duplication of the entire backbone.   We observe that low-quality videos, despite degradation, retain reliable structural information such as layout and motion, and that such structural content is largely domain-agnostic. This suggests that a frozen generator can perform VSR when the input structure is properly aligned to its embedding space. Building on this insight, we propose LiteVSR, a minimalist framework that performs VSR using a completely frozen Diffusion Transformer (DiT) with a lightweight State-Aware Adapter. The adapter employs a dual-stream architecture that jointly processes static structural cues from the low-quality input and dynamic cues from intermediate denoising states through time-dependent cross-attention, enabling adaptive transition from structural alignment to texture refinement as denoising proceeds. LiteVSR achieves comparable restoration quality with only 12.68\\% trainable parameters and 12 GPU-hours of training on a single A100.</p>","absKo":"<p>대규모 사전 학습 video generator는 Video Super-Resolution (VSR)을 위한 강력한 prior를 제공하지만, 이를 적응시키는 것은 여전히 계산적으로 매우 부담스럽다. 전체 fine-tuning은 막대한 자원을 요구하고, ControlNet-style adapter는 encoder-decoder hierarchy가 없는 현대 Diffusion Transformer (DiT)에서는 전체 backbone을 복제해야 하므로 효율성 우위를 잃는다. 우리는 품질이 낮은 video가 손상되었음에도 layout과 motion 같은 신뢰할 수 있는 구조 정보를 보존하며, 이러한 구조적 내용은 대체로 domain-agnostic하다는 점을 관찰했다. 이는 입력 구조가 embedding space에 적절히 정렬되기만 하면 frozen generator가 VSR을 수행할 수 있음을 시사한다. 이 통찰을 바탕으로, 우리는 완전히 frozen된 Diffusion Transformer (DiT)와 경량 State-Aware Adapter를 사용하여 VSR을 수행하는 최소주의 framework인 LiteVSR를 제안한다. 이 adapter는 low-quality input의 정적 구조 단서와 중간 denoising state의 동적 단서를 time-dependent cross-attention으로 공동 처리하는 dual-stream architecture를 사용하며, denoising이 진행됨에 따라 구조 정렬에서 texture refinement로 적응적으로 전환할 수 있게 한다. LiteVSR은 단 12.68\\%의 학습 가능한 parameter와 단일 A100에서의 12 GPU-hour 학습만으로 유사한 복원 품질을 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"62816","en":"LayerT2V: A Unified Multi-Layer Video Generation Framework","ko":"LayerT2V: 통합형 멀티 레이어 비디오 생성 프레임워크","authors":"Guangzhao Li, Kangrui Cen, Baixuan Zhao, Yi Xin, Siqi Luo, Guangtao Zhai, Lei Zhang, Xiaohong Liu","pos":"#916","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=czTbPdmvtT","abs":"<p>Text-to-video generation has advanced rapidly, but existing methods typically output only the final composited video and lack editable layered representations, limiting their use in professional workflows. We propose \\textbf{LayerT2V}, a unified multi-layer video generation framework that produces multiple semantically consistent outputs in a single inference pass: the full video, an independent background layer, and multiple foreground RGB layers with corresponding alpha mattes. Our key insight is that recent video generation backbones use high compression in both time and space, enabling us to serialize multiple layer representations along the temporal dimension and jointly model them on a shared generation trajectory. This turns cross-layer consistency into an intrinsic objective, improving semantic alignment and temporal coherence. To mitigate layer ambiguity and conditional leakage, we augment a shared DiT backbone with LayerAdaLN and layer-aware cross-attention modulation. LayerT2V is trained in three stages: alpha mask VAE adaptation, joint multi-layer learning, and multi-foreground extension. We also introduce \\textbf{VidLayer}, the first large-scale dataset for multi-layer video generation. Extensive experiments demonstrate that LayerT2V substantially outperforms prior methods in visual fidelity, temporal consistency, and cross-layer coherence. To facilitate future research, we will release the code and dataset upon publication.</p>","absKo":"<p>Text-to-video generation은 빠르게 발전했지만, 기존 방법은 대개 최종 합성된 비디오만 출력하고 편집 가능한 layered representation은 제공하지 않아 전문 워크플로에서의 활용이 제한된다. 우리는 단일 inference pass에서 여러 semantically consistent output을 생성하는 통합 multi-layer video generation framework인 \\textbf{LayerT2V}를 제안한다. 이 framework는 전체 비디오, 독립적인 background layer, 그리고 대응되는 alpha matte를 갖는 여러 foreground RGB layer를 생성한다. 핵심 통찰은 최근 video generation backbone이 시간적·공간적으로 높은 compression을 사용한다는 점이며, 이를 통해 여러 layer representation을 temporal dimension에 따라 직렬화하고 공유 generation trajectory 위에서 공동으로 모델링할 수 있다. 이는 cross-layer consistency를 내재적 목표로 바꾸어 semantic alignment와 temporal coherence를 향상시킨다. layer ambiguity와 conditional leakage를 완화하기 위해, 우리는 shared DiT backbone에 LayerAdaLN과 layer-aware cross-attention modulation을 추가한다. LayerT2V는 alpha mask VAE adaptation, joint multi-layer learning, multi-foreground extension의 세 단계로 학습된다. 또한 우리는 multi-layer video generation을 위한 최초의 대규모 데이터셋인 \\textbf{VidLayer}를 소개한다. 광범위한 실험은 LayerT2V가 visual fidelity, temporal consistency, cross-layer coherence에서 기존 방법을 크게 능가함을 보여준다. 향후 연구를 촉진하기 위해, 공개 시점에 코드와 데이터셋을 배포할 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"61708","en":"Planar Symmetric Pattern Generation","ko":"평면 대칭 패턴 생성","authors":"Ning Lin, Luxi Chen, Huaguan Chen, Jiacheng Cen, Chongxuan Li, Wenbing Huang, Hao Sun","pos":"#2509","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=nbU2LNYdZN","abs":"<p>Generating objects with specific symmetries is essential in various real-world scenarios, with the creation of patterns exhibiting planar group symmetries being a representative task. However, adapting existing 2D continuous representations to enforce symmetry remains a significant challenge, as the transformation of non-reflective group elements may disrupt continuity. To overcome this limitation, we propose a novel symmetric continuous representation framework for arbitrary planar groups. Our method transforms any underlying 2D continuous representation into a symmetric one while strictly preserving continuity. We provide the mathematical formulation of this representation, demonstrate its universal approximation capability for symmetric functions, and detail the construction methodology. We validate our approach through three distinct generation tasks: general symmetric pattern design, connectivity-preserving paper-cutting design, and mechanically-constrained geometric stylized patterns. Experimental results confirm that our representation enables precise and effective symmetry control in pattern generation.</p>","absKo":"특정 symmetry를 가진 object를 생성하는 것은 다양한 실제 응용에서 중요하며, planar group symmetry를 보이는 pattern을 만드는 작업이 대표적인 예이다. 그러나 기존 2D continuous representation을 symmetry를 강제하도록 적응시키는 것은 여전히 큰 도전인데, 비반사(non-reflective) group element의 변환이 continuity를 깨뜨릴 수 있기 때문이다. 이러한 한계를 극복하기 위해, 우리는 임의의 planar group을 위한 새로운 symmetric continuous representation framework를 제안한다. 우리의 방법은 어떤 기반 2D continuous representation도 continuity를 엄격히 보존하면서 symmetric한 representation으로 변환한다. 우리는 이 representation의 수학적 정식화를 제시하고, symmetric function에 대한 universal approximation capability를 보이며, 구성 방법을 상세히 설명한다. 우리는 일반적인 symmetric pattern design, connectivity-preserving paper-cutting design, 그리고 mechanically-constrained geometric stylized pattern의 세 가지 서로 다른 생성 과제를 통해 접근법을 검증한다. 실험 결과는 우리의 representation이 pattern generation에서 정밀하고 효과적인 symmetry 제어를 가능하게 함을 확인한다.</p>"},{"id":"65787","en":"Minibatch Optimal Transport and Perplexity Bound Estimation in Discrete Flow Matching","ko":"이산 Flow Matching에서의 미니배치 최적 수송과 Perplexity 경계 추정","authors":"Etrit Haxholli, Yeti Z. Gurbuz, Oğul Can, Eli Waxman","pos":"#2616","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=A8rmJlSET9","abs":"<p>Discrete flow matching, a recent framework for modeling categorical data, has shown competitive performance with autoregressive models. However, unlike continuous flow matching, the rectification strategy cannot be applied due to the stochasticity of discrete paths, necessitating alternative methods to minimize state transitions. We propose a dynamic-optimal-transport-like minimization objective and derive its Kantorovich formulation for discrete flows with convex interpolants, where transport cost depends solely on inter-state similarity and can be optimized via minibatch strategies. We show that such methods can reduce the number of transitions up to 8 times (1024 to 128) to reach the same generative perplexity without compromising diversity. Additionally, path nondeterminism in discrete flows precludes an instantaneous change-of-variables analogue, preventing precise probability estimation available to continuous flows. We therefore propose two upper bounds on perplexity, enabling principled training, evaluation and model comparison. Finally, we introduce Multimask Flows which outperform masked flows in generative perplexity without compromising diversity, particularly when utilizing minibatch Optimal Transport.</p>"},{"id":"60760","en":"PromptDyG: Test-Time Prompt Adaptation on Dynamic Graphs","ko":"PromptDyG: 동적 그래프에서의 Test-Time Prompt Adaptation","authors":"Guoguo Ai, Chaoxi Niu, Hui Yan, Joey Tianyi Zhou, Yew Soon ONG, Guansong Pang","pos":"#4003","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=wu36B3DqNM","abs":"<p>Activities in numerous evolving systems can be represented as dynamic graphs in snapshot form at different time intervals, i.e., discrete-time dynamic graphs (DTDGs). Existing methods show impressive advances in capturing historical temporal evolution patterns in DTDGs, but they focus on addressing an offline learning setting, where models are trained using historical snapshots once and then evaluated to all subsequent graph snapshots without further updating. This fails to capture 1) the nature of evolving complexities across graph snapshots and 2) the distribution shift in the testing graph snapshots. To address these problems, we propose PromptDyG, a novel framework that leverages unsupervised test-time Prompt adaptation for Dynamic Graph learning under a live-update online setting. The key insight is that an expressive dynamic graph prompt can be learned on a frozen backbone via minimization of feature-wise, label-free entropy to efficiently and continuously model the evolving patterns. We show theoretically that this unsupervised prompt adaptation can guarantee a larger similarity margin between positive and negative pairs, facilitating more accurate dynamic predictions. It is further confirmed by our extensive empirical results on six benchmark datasets that show consistent and significant improvements of PromptDyG over state-of-the-art baselines. Code is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/PromptDyG-3887.</p>","absKo":"<p>여러 진화하는 시스템의 활동은 서로 다른 시간 간격에서의 snapshot 형태, 즉 discrete-time dynamic graph (DTDG)로 표현될 수 있다. 기존 방법들은 DTDG에서 과거의 temporal evolution pattern을 포착하는 데 있어 인상적인 발전을 보였지만, 모델을 과거 snapshot으로 한 번 학습한 뒤 추가 갱신 없이 이후의 모든 graph snapshot을 평가하는 offline learning setting에 초점을 맞춘다. 이는 1) graph snapshot 전반에 걸쳐 진화하는 복잡성의 특성과 2) 테스트 graph snapshot에서의 distribution shift를 포착하지 못한다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 live-update online setting에서 Dynamic Graph learning을 위한 unsupervised test-time Prompt adaptation을 활용하는 새로운 프레임워크 PromptDyG를 제안한다. 핵심 아이디어는 feature-wise, label-free entropy의 최소화를 통해 frozen backbone 위에서 표현력 있는 dynamic graph prompt를 학습함으로써, 진화하는 pattern을 효율적이고 지속적으로 모델링할 수 있다는 것이다. 우리는 이 unsupervised prompt adaptation이 positive pair와 negative pair 사이의 similarity margin을 더 크게 보장하여, 더 정확한 dynamic prediction을 가능하게 함을 이론적으로 보인다. 또한 6개의 benchmark dataset에 대한 광범위한 실험 결과는 PromptDyG가 state-of-the-art baseline에 비해 일관되고 유의미한 성능 향상을 보인다는 점을 확인해준다. 코드는 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/PromptDyG-3887 에서 제공된다.</p>"},{"id":"60619","en":"What Information Matters? Graph Out-of-Distribution Detection via Tri-Component Information Decomposition","ko":"어떤 정보가 중요한가? 삼중 구성 정보 분해를 통한 그래프 Out-of-Distribution 탐지","authors":"Danny Wang, Ruihong Qiu, Zi Huang","pos":"#2303","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ySUfgY6twT","abs":"<p>Graph neural networks are widely used for node classification, but they remain vulnerable to out-of-distribution (OOD) shifts in node features and graph structure. Prior work established that methods trained with standard supervised learning (SL) objectives tend to capture spurious signals from either features and/or structure, leaving the model fragile under distributional changes. To address this, we propose \\textsc{Tide}, a novel and effective \\underline{T}ri-Component \\underline{I}nformation \\underline{De}composition framework that explicitly decomposes information into \\textit{feature-specific, structure-specific and joint} components. \\textsc{Tide} aims to preserve only the label-relevant part of the joint information while filtering out spurious feature- and structure-specific information, thereby enhancing the separation between in-distribution (ID) and OOD nodes. Beyond the framework, we provide theoretical and empirical analyses showing that an information bottleneck objective is preferable to standard SL for graph OOD detection, with higher ID confidence and a greater entropy gap between ID and OOD data. Extensive experiments across seven datasets confirm the efficacy of \\textsc{Tide}, achieving up to a 34% improvement in FPR95 over strong baselines while maintaining competitive ID accuracy. Code will be released upon acceptance.</p>","absKo":"<p>Graph neural network는 node classification에 널리 사용되지만, node feature와 graph structure의 out-of-distribution (OOD) shift에는 여전히 취약하다. 선행 연구는 standard supervised learning (SL) objective로 학습된 방법이 feature 및/또는 structure에서 오는 spurious signal을 포착하는 경향이 있어, distribution 변화 아래에서 model이 취약해진다는 점을 보였다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 정보를 \\textit{feature-specific, structure-specific, joint} component로 명시적으로 분해하는 새로운 효과적인 \\underline{T}ri-Component \\underline{I}nformation \\underline{De}composition framework인 \\textsc{Tide}를 제안한다. \\textsc{Tide}는 label과 관련된 joint information의 부분만 보존하고, spurious feature- 및 structure-specific information은 걸러내어 in-distribution (ID) node와 OOD node 사이의 분리를 강화하는 것을 목표로 한다. 프레임워크를 넘어, 우리는 information bottleneck objective가 graph OOD detection에서 standard SL보다 더 적절하며, 더 높은 ID confidence와 ID 데이터와 OOD 데이터 사이의 더 큰 entropy gap을 제공한다는 이론적·실증적 분석을 제시한다. 7개 데이터셋에 걸친 광범위한 실험은 \\textsc{Tide}의 효용을 확인해 주며, 강력한 baseline 대비 FPR95를 최대 34%까지 개선하면서도 경쟁력 있는 ID 정확도를 유지한다. 코드는 승인 후 공개될 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"64132","en":"Sheaf Neural Networks on SPD Manifolds: Second-Order Geometric Representation Learning","ko":"SPD 매니폴드 상의 Sheaf 신경망: 2차 기하학적 표현 학습","authors":"Yuhan Peng, Junwen Dong, Yuzhi Zeng, Hao Li, Ce Ju, Huitao Feng, Diaaeldin Taha, Anna Wienhard, Kelin Xia","pos":"#2305","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Qbe2cfNfn1","abs":"<p>Graph neural networks face two fundamental challenges rooted in the linear structure of Euclidean vector spaces: (1) Current  architectures represent geometry through vectors (directions, gradients), yet many tasks require matrix-valued representations that capture relationships between directions—such as how atomic orientations covary in a molecule. These second-order representations are naturally  captured by points on the symmetric positive definite matrices (SPD) manifold; (2) Standard message passing applies shared transformations across edges. Sheaf neural networks address this via edge-specific transformations, but existing formulations remain confined to vector spaces and therefore cannot propagate matrix-valued features. We address both challenges by developing the first  sheaf neural network operates natively on the SPD manifold. Our key insight is that the SPD manifold admits a Lie group structure, enabling well-posed analogs of sheaf operators without projecting to Euclidean space. Theoretically, we prove that SPD-valued sheaves are strictly more expressive than Euclidean sheaves: they admit consistent configurations (global sections) that vector-valued  sheaves cannot represent, directly translating to richer learned representations. Empirically, our sheaf convolution  transforms effectively rank-1 directional inputs into full-rank matrices encoding local geometric structure. Our dual-stream architecture achieves SOTA on 6/7 MoleculeNet benchmarks, with the sheaf framework providing consistent depth robustness.</p>","absKo":"Graph neural networks는 Euclidean vector space의 선형 구조에 뿌리를 둔 두 가지 근본적 도전에 직면한다. (1) 현재 architecture는 geometry를 vector(방향, gradient)로 표현하지만, 많은 task는 원자 배향이 분자 내에서 어떻게 공변하는지와 같이 방향들 간의 관계를 포착하는 matrix-valued representation을 필요로 한다. 이러한 second-order representation은 symmetric positive definite matrices (SPD) manifold 위의 점으로 자연스럽게 포착된다. (2) 표준 message passing은 edge 전반에 걸쳐 shared transformation을 적용한다. Sheaf neural network는 edge-specific transformation을 통해 이를 해결하지만, 기존 formulation은 여전히 vector space에 국한되어 있어 matrix-valued feature를 전파할 수 없다. 우리는 SPD manifold 위에서 native하게 동작하는 최초의 sheaf neural network를 개발함으로써 이 두 문제를 모두 해결한다. 핵심 통찰은 SPD manifold가 Lie group structure를 허용하여 Euclidean space로 투영하지 않고도 sheaf operator의 well-posed analog를 가능하게 한다는 점이다. 이론적으로, 우리는 SPD-valued sheaf가 Euclidean sheaf보다 엄밀히 더 expressive하다는 것을 증명한다. 즉, vector-valued sheaf가 표현할 수 없는 consistent configuration(global section)를 허용하며, 이는 더 풍부한 learned representation으로 직접 이어진다. 실험적으로, 우리의 sheaf convolution은 효과적으로 rank-1 directional input을 local geometric structure를 인코딩하는 full-rank matrix로 변환한다. 우리의 dual-stream architecture는 6/7 MoleculeNet benchmark에서 SOTA를 달성했으며, sheaf framework는 일관된 depth robustness를 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"68832","en":"SE3Set: Harnessing Equivariant Hypergraph Neural Networks for Molecular Representation Learning","ko":"SE3Set: 분자 표현 학습을 위한 Equivariant Hypergraph Neural Network 활용","authors":"Hongfei Wu, Lijun Wu, Guoqing Liu, Zhirong Liu, Bin Shao, Zun Wang","pos":"#1115","abs":"<p>In this paper, we develop SE3Set, an SE(3) equivariant hypergraph neural network architecture tailored for advanced molecular representation learning. Hypergraphs are not merely an extension of traditional graphs; they are pivotal for modeling high-order relationships, a capability that conventional equivariant graph-based methods lack due to their inherent limitations in representing intricate many-body interactions. To achieve this, we first construct hypergraphs by proposing a new fragmentation method that considers both chemical and three-dimensional spatial information of the molecular system. We then design SE3Set, which incorporates equivariance into the hypergraph neural network. This ensures that the learned molecular representations are invariant to spatial transformations, thereby providing robustness essential for the accurate prediction of molecular properties. SE3Set has shown performance on par with state-of-the-art (SOTA) models for small molecule datasets like QM9 and MD17. It demonstrates outstanding performance on the MD22 dataset, achieving a remarkable ~20\\% improvement in accuracy across all molecules. Furthermore, on the OE62 dataset, SE3Set outperforms all short-range models. We also conducted a detailed analysis of OE62, highlighting the prevalence of complex many-body interactions in large molecules. This exceptional performance of SE3Set across diverse molecular structures underscores its transformative potential in computational chemistry, offering a route to more accurate and physically nuanced modeling. The code of this work is available at https://github.com/Navantock/SE3Set.</p>"},{"id":"61316","en":"Identifying and Correcting Label Noise for Robust GNNs via Influence Contradiction","ko":"Influence Contradiction을 통한 강건한 GNN을 위한 라벨 노이즈 식별과 보정","authors":"Wei Ju, Wei Zhang, Siyu Yi, Zhengyang Mao, Yifan Wang, Jingyang Yuan, Zhiping Xiao, Ziyue Qiao, Ming Zhang","pos":"#207","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=rR97qOfb7W","abs":"<p>Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) have shown remarkable capabilities in learning from graph-structured data with various applications such as social analysis and bioinformatics. However, the presence of label noise in real scenarios poses a significant challenge in learning robust GNNs, and their effectiveness can be severely impacted when dealing with noisy labels on graphs, often stemming from annotation errors or inconsistencies. To address this, in this paper we propose a novel approach called ICGNN that harnesses the structure information of the graph to effectively alleviate the challenges posed by noisy labels. Specifically, we first design a novel noise indicator that measures the influence contradiction score (ICS) based on the graph diffusion matrix to quantify the credibility of nodes with clean labels, such that nodes with higher ICS values are more likely to be detected as having noisy labels. Then we leverage the Gaussian mixture model to precisely detect whether the label of a node is noisy or not. Additionally, we develop a soft strategy to combine the predictions from neighboring nodes on the graph to correct the detected noisy labels. At last, pseudo-labeling for abundant unlabeled nodes is incorporated to provide auxiliary supervision signals and guide the model optimization. Experiments on benchmark datasets show the superiority of our approach over competitive baselines in noisy label scenarios.</p>","absKo":"<p>Graph Neural Networks(GNNs)는 social analysis와 bioinformatics와 같은 다양한 응용에서 graph-structured data를 학습하는 데 뛰어난 능력을 보여왔다. 그러나 실제 시나리오에서의 label noise는 robust GNN을 학습하는 데 중요한 도전 과제가 되며, graph 상의 noisy label을 다룰 때 그 효과가 심각하게 저하될 수 있는데, 이는 흔히 annotation error나 불일치에서 기인한다. 이를 해결하기 위해 본 논문에서는 graph의 structure information을 활용하여 noisy label이 초래하는 문제를 효과적으로 완화하는 ICGNN이라는 새로운 접근법을 제안한다. 구체적으로, 먼저 graph diffusion matrix를 기반으로 influence contradiction score(ICS)를 측정하는 새로운 noise indicator를 설계하여 clean label을 가진 node의 신뢰도를 정량화하고, ICS 값이 더 높은 node일수록 noisy label을 가진 것으로 탐지될 가능성이 높도록 한다. سپس Gaussian mixture model을 활용하여 node의 label이 noisy한지 여부를 정밀하게 탐지한다. 추가로, graph 상의 이웃 node들로부터의 예측을 부드럽게 결합하는 soft strategy를 개발하여 탐지된 noisy label을 교정한다. 마지막으로, 풍부한 unlabeled node에 대한 pseudo-labeling을 통합하여 보조 supervision signal을 제공하고 model optimization을 유도한다. benchmark dataset에서의 실험은 noisy label 시나리오에서 경쟁력 있는 baseline에 비해 우리 방법의 우수성을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"65422","en":"When Do Graph Foundation Models Transfer? A Data-Centric Theory","ko":"Graph Foundation Model은 언제 전이되는가? 데이터 중심 이론","authors":"Jiajun Zhu, Ying Chen, Peihao Wang, Yixuan He, Pan Li, Aditya Akella, Zhangyang “Atlas” Wang","pos":"#2302","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Dp0YWzPAGM","abs":"<p>Graph foundation models (GFMs) aim to reuse a single backbone across diverse graph domains, yet their transfer is often uneven and can exhibit negative transfer. While most prior work improves transfer through architectural or adaptation choices, we ask a data-centric question: <em>which properties of two graph domains determine how much a fixed representation model changes its outputs?</em> Using a graphon-based continuous limit for dense graphs, we show that for both set-based and message-passing tokenizations, any Lipschitz backbone admits an explicit decomposition of cross-domain output shift into (i) graph-specific finite-sample approximation terms and (ii) an intrinsic, relabeling-invariant domain discrepancy capturing structural mismatch. A key ingredient is positional-encoding (PE) stability: we establish stability guarantees for spectral PEs and highlight contrasting behaviors of eigenvector- versus subspace-based PEs. Experiments on synthetic and real graphs validate the theory and translate the decomposition into guidance for data curation in GFM transfer.</p>"},{"id":"61099","en":"Towards Generative Graph Matching for Graph Edit Distance Computation","ko":"Graph Edit Distance 계산을 위한 생성적 Graph Matching을 향하여","authors":"Wei Huang, Hanchen Wang, Dong Wen, Wenjie Zhang, Ying Zhang, Xuemin Lin","pos":"#2304","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=thuyfHsRIu","abs":"Graph Edit Distance (GED), which aims to find an edit path with minimum number of edit operations to transform one graph into another, is a fundamental NP-hard problem and a widely used graph similarity measure. Recent matching-based hybrid approaches have demonstrated better scalability than A* search-based hybrids by reformulating GED as a graph matching problem. In these methods, a neural network predicts a single deterministic node matching matrix, from which top-$k$ node mappings are extracted iteratively to derive candidate edit paths. However, these methods often suffer from highly correlated candidates that easily lead to suboptimal solutions, while the iterative extraction becomes inefficient for large $k$. In this paper, we propose DiffGED, the first generative approach for GED computation. Specifically, we formulate the graph matching problem as a generative task, and employ a diffusion-based model to generate multiple diverse node matching matrices simultaneously, from which diverse node mappings can be efficiently extracted. The generative diversity introduced by the diffusion process enables DiffGED to avoid suboptimal solutions and achieve superior solution quality close to the exact solution. Experiments on real-world datasets show that DiffGED generates multiple diverse edit paths with accuracy comparable to exact solutions, while running faster than existing hybrid approaches.","absKo":"Graph Edit Distance (GED)는 한 graph를 다른 graph로 변환하기 위해 최소 개수의 edit operation을 갖는 edit path를 찾는 것을 목표로 하는, 기본적인 NP-hard problem이며 널리 사용되는 graph similarity measure이다. 최근의 matching-based hybrid approach는 GED를 graph matching problem으로 재정식화함으로써 A* search-based hybrid보다 더 나은 scalability를 보여주었다. 이러한 방법들에서 neural network는 하나의 deterministic node matching matrix를 예측하고, 여기서 top-$k$ node mapping을 반복적으로 추출하여 candidate edit path를 도출한다. 그러나 이러한 방법은 종종 서로 강하게 상관된 candidate로 인해 최적 이하의 해에 쉽게 빠지며, 반복적 추출은 큰 $k$에서 비효율적이 된다. 본 논문에서는 GED 계산을 위한 최초의 generative approach인 DiffGED를 제안한다. 구체적으로, graph matching problem을 generative task로 정식화하고, diffusion-based model을 사용하여 여러 개의 diverse node matching matrix를 동시에 생성하며, 이를 통해 다양한 node mapping을 효율적으로 추출할 수 있게 한다. diffusion process가 도입하는 generative diversity는 DiffGED가 suboptimal solution을 피하고 exact solution에 가까운 더 우수한 해 품질을 달성하도록 만든다. 실제 데이터셋에서의 실험은 DiffGED가 exact solution과 동등한 수준의 정확도로 여러 개의 다양한 edit path를 생성하면서, 기존 hybrid approach보다 더 빠르게 동작함을 보여준다."},{"id":"63249","en":"Revisiting Positive Samples in Graph Contrastive Learning: From the Perspective of Message Passing","ko":"그래프 대조 학습에서 양성 샘플 재고: 메시지 전달 관점에서","authors":"Lianze Shan, Ningchong Wang, Jitao Zhao, Di Jin, Dongxiao He","pos":"#2307","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=YkUsqcPYkU","abs":"<p>Graph Contrastive Learning (GCL), which trains graph encoders by maximizing similarity between positive samples and minimizing it between negative ones, has emerged as a mainstream graph pre-training paradigm. It is widely recognized that positive samples are essential in GCLs. Ideally, maximizing the similarity of positive samples enables graph encoders to capture intrinsic semantic and patterns of graph data. However, we discover an interesting phenomenon: GCLs can achieve competitive performance even without positive samples. This motivates us to revisit the fundamental mechanism of positive samples in GCLs. From the perspective of Dirichlet energy, we theoretically finds that message passing, a key mechanism in graph encoders, trivializes the maximization of positive samples, preventing GCLs from effectively learning from positive samples. To address this, we propose SPGCL to mitigate the trivialization caused by message passing and restore the learning efficacy of positive samples. Specifically, we find that high Dirichlet energy features help positive samples provide effective learning signals while low Dirichlet energy features contribute little to positive learning signal but is useful for positive sampling. Based on this, SPGCL propagates only high Dirichlet energy features and uses low energy features to construct a probability matrix for reliable positive sampling. Extensive experiments demonstrate the effectiveness of SPGCL.</p>","absKo":"<p>Graph Contrastive Learning(GCL)은 positive sample 간 유사도를 최대화하고 negative sample 간 유사도를 최소화함으로써 graph encoder를 학습하는 방식으로, graph pre-training의 주류 패러다임으로 부상했다. GCL에서 positive sample이 필수적이라는 점은 널리 알려져 있다. 이상적으로는 positive sample의 유사도를 최대화함으로써 graph encoder가 graph 데이터의 내재적 semantic과 pattern을 포착할 수 있다. 그러나 우리는 흥미로운 현상을 발견했다. GCL은 positive sample이 없어도 경쟁력 있는 성능을 달성할 수 있다. 이는 GCL에서 positive sample의 근본 메커니즘을 다시 살펴보게 만든다. Dirichlet energy 관점에서, 우리는 graph encoder의 핵심 메커니즘인 message passing이 positive sample 최대화의 효과를 무의미하게 만들어 GCL이 positive sample로부터 효과적으로 학습하지 못하게 한다는 점을 이론적으로 보인다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 message passing으로 인한 무의미화를 완화하고 positive sample의 학습 효능을 복원하는 SPGCL을 제안한다. 구체적으로, 우리는 Dirichlet energy가 높은 feature가 positive sample이 효과적인 학습 신호를 제공하는 데 도움이 되는 반면, Dirichlet energy가 낮은 feature는 positive learning signal에는 거의 기여하지 않지만 positive sampling에는 유용하다는 점을 발견한다. 이를 바탕으로 SPGCL은 Dirichlet energy가 높은 feature만 전파하고, 낮은 energy feature를 사용해 신뢰할 수 있는 positive sampling을 위한 probability matrix를 구성한다. 광범위한 실험은 SPGCL의 효과를 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"65396","en":"Rethinking GNNs and Missing Features: Challenges, Evaluation and a Robust Solution","ko":"GNN과 결측 특징 재고: 도전 과제, 평가, 그리고 강건한 해법","authors":"Francesco Ferrini, Veronica Lachi, Antonio Longa, Bruno Lepri, Akiyoshi Matono, Andrea Passerini, Xin Liu, Manfred Jaeger","pos":"#2308","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=E4gftzjqoh","abs":"<p>Handling missing node features is a key challenge for deploying Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) in real-world domains such as healthcare and sensor networks. Existing studies mostly address relatively benign scenarios, namely benchmark datasets with (a) high-dimensional but sparse node features and (b) incomplete data generated under Missing Completely At Random (MCAR) mechanisms. For (a), we theoretically prove that high sparsity substantially limits the information loss caused by missingness, making all models appear robust and preventing a meaningful comparison of their performance. To overcome this limitation, we introduce one synthetic and three real-world datasets with dense, semantically meaningful features. For (b), we move beyond MCAR and design evaluation protocols with more realistic missingness mechanisms. Moreover, we provide a theoretical background to state explicit assumptions on the missingness process and analyze their implications for different methods. Building on this analysis, we propose GNNmim, a simple yet effective baseline for node classification with incomplete feature data. Experiments show that GNNmim is competitive with respect to specialized architectures across diverse datasets and missingness regimes.</p>"},{"id":"60957","en":"Rethinking Contrastive Learning for Graph Collaborative Filtering: Limitations and A Simple Remedy","ko":"Graph Collaborative Filtering을 위한 Contrastive Learning 재고: 한계와 간단한 해결책","authors":"Geon Lee, Sunwoo Kim, Kyungho Kim, Kijung Shin","pos":"#2309","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=v2rdJBVVEt","abs":"<p>Graph collaborative filtering (GCF) is a dominant paradigm in recommender systems, where contrastive learning (CL) objectives such as the Sampled Softmax (SSM) loss are widely used for optimization. However, it remains unclear how CL interacts with the prediction mechanism of GCF. By unfolding the prediction mechanism of GCF, we show that the user-item prediction score is computed by aggregating learnable weights over a large number of neighbor pairs formed by the multi-hop neighbors of the user and the item. This analysis implies that effective optimization critically depends on which neighbor pairs are upweighted during training. Empirically, we find that effective recommendation is achievable by selectively upweighting only a small subset of neighbor pairs whose constituent neighbors are structurally similar to the target user and item, and that the effect of such selective upweighting varies across different neighbor pair types. Based on these findings, we analyze SSM and identify key limitations in its neighbor pair weight update dynamics. To address these limitations, we propose NT-SSM, an effective and principled CL objective that induces type-aware neighbor pair weight update dynamics. Experiments demonstrate consistent performance improvements over SSM across multiple datasets and GCF models.</p>","absKo":"<p>Graph collaborative filtering (GCF)는 추천 시스템에서 지배적인 패러다임이며, Sampled Softmax (SSM) loss와 같은 contrastive learning (CL) 목적함수가 최적화에 널리 사용된다. 그러나 CL이 GCF의 예측 메커니즘과 어떻게 상호작용하는지는 여전히 명확하지 않다. GCF의 예측 메커니즘을 펼쳐서 분석함으로써, user-item 예측 점수는 user와 item의 multi-hop neighbor로 형성된 다수의 neighbor pair에 대해 학습 가능한 가중치를 집계하여 계산됨을 보인다. 이 분석은 효과적인 최적화가 학습 동안 어떤 neighbor pair가 더 높은 가중치를 받는지에 결정적으로 의존함을 시사한다. 실험적으로, 우리는 구성하는 neighbor가 목표 user와 item과 구조적으로 유사한 소수의 neighbor pair만 선택적으로 upweighting해도 효과적인 추천이 가능하며, 이러한 선택적 upweighting의 효과는 서로 다른 neighbor pair 유형에 따라 달라진다는 것을 발견했다. 이러한 발견을 바탕으로 SSM을 분석하고, neighbor pair 가중치 갱신 동역학에서의 핵심 한계를 식별한다. 이러한 한계를 해결하기 위해, type-aware neighbor pair weight update dynamics를 유도하는 효과적이고 원리에 기반한 CL 목적함수인 NT-SSM을 제안한다. 실험은 여러 데이터셋과 GCF 모델 전반에서 SSM 대비 일관된 성능 향상을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"67213","en":"Position: Graph Condensation Needs a Reset—Move Beyond Full-dataset Training and Model-Dependence","ko":"Position: Graph Condensation에는 재설정이 필요하다 — Full-dataset 학습과 모델 의존성을 넘어서라","authors":"Mridul Gupta, Samyak Jain, Vansh Ramani, HARIPRASAD KODAMANA, Sayan Ranu","pos":"#2310","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=BivTo9DoJJ","abs":"<p>Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) are powerful tools for learning from graph-structured data, but their scalability is increasingly strained by the size of real-world graphs in domains like recommender systems, fraud detection, and molecular biology. Graph condensation—the task of generating a smaller synthetic graph that retains the performance of models trained on the original—has emerged as a promising solution. However, the dominant approach of gradient matching introduces a fundamental contradiction: it requires training on the full dataset to create the compressed version, thereby undermining the goal of efficiency. Worse still, these methods suffer from high computational overhead, poor generalization across GNN architectures, and brittle reliance on specific model configurations. Equally concerning is the community's reliance on misleading evaluation protocols such as node compression ratios, which fail to reflect true resource savings, condensation overhead, and illusory application to neural architecture search. These shortcomings are not incidental—they are systemic, and they obstruct meaningful progress.  In this position paper, we argue that graph condensation, in its current form, needs a reset. We call for moving beyond full-dataset training and model-dependent design, and instead advocate for methods that are lightweight, architecture-agnostic, and practically deployable. By identifying key methodological flaws and outlining concrete research directions, we aim to reorient the field toward approaches that deliver on the true promise of condensation: efficient, generalizable, and usable GNN training at scale.</p>"},{"id":"62208","en":"Normality Calibration in Semi-supervised Graph Anomaly Detection","ko":"반지도학습 그래프 이상치 탐지에서 Normality Calibration","authors":"Guolei Zeng, Hezhe Qiao, Guoguo Ai, Jinsong Guo, Guansong Pang","pos":"#2311","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ifjUMvvY05","abs":"Semi-supervised graph anomaly detection (GAD), which assumes a subset of annotated normal nodes available during training, is among the most widely explored applications. However, the normality learned by existing semi-supervised GAD methods is limited to the labeled normal nodes, often inclining to overfitting the given patterns, thereby leading to high detection errors, such as high false positives. To overcome this limitation, we propose $GraphNC$, a graph normality calibration framework that leverages both labeled and unlabeled data to calibrate the normality from a teacher (a pre-trained semi-supervised GAD model) jointly in anomaly score and representation spaces. GraphNC includes two main components, anomaly score distribution alignment ($ScoreDA$) and perturbation-based normality regularization ($NormReg$). ScoreDA optimizes the anomaly scores of our model by aligning them with the score distribution yielded by the teacher. Due to accurate scores in most of the normal nodes and part of the anomaly nodes in the teacher, the alignment effectively pulls the anomaly scores of the two classes toward the two ends, resulting in more separable anomaly scores. To mitigate the misleading by inaccurate scores from the teacher, NormReg is designed to regularize the normality in representation space, making the representations of normal nodes more compact by minimizing a perturbation-guided consistency loss solely on the labeled nodes. Comprehensive experiments on six benchmarks demonstrate that GraphNC (1) consistently and substantially enhances the performance of teacher models from different GAD methods (2) achieves new state-of-the-art performance.","absKo":"semi-supervised graph anomaly detection(GAD)은 학습 중 일부 annotated normal node가 주어진다고 가정하며, 가장 널리 연구된 응용 중 하나이다. 그러나 기존 semi-supervised GAD 방법이 학습하는 normality는 labeled normal node에만 한정되어 있어, 주어진 패턴에 과적합되기 쉽고, 그 결과 높은 false positive와 같은 큰 탐지 오류를 초래한다. 이러한 한계를 극복하기 위해, 우리는 labeled 및 unlabeled data를 모두 활용하여 teacher(pre-trained semi-supervised GAD model)로부터 anomaly score 공간과 representation 공간 양쪽에서 normality를 공동으로 calibration하는 graph normality calibration framework인 $GraphNC$를 제안한다. GraphNC는 anomaly score distribution alignment($ScoreDA$)과 perturbation-based normality regularization($NormReg$)라는 두 가지 주요 구성요소를 포함한다. ScoreDA는 teacher가 생성한 score distribution과 정렬함으로써 우리 모델의 anomaly score를 최적화한다. teacher는 대부분의 normal node와 일부 anomaly node에 대해 정확한 score를 제공하므로, 이러한 정렬은 두 class의 anomaly score를 양 끝으로 효과적으로 끌어당겨 더 잘 분리되는 anomaly score를 만든다. teacher의 부정확한 score로 인한 오도를 완화하기 위해, NormReg는 representation space에서 normality를 regularize하도록 설계되었으며, labeled node에 대해서만 perturbation-guided consistency loss를 최소화하여 normal node의 representation이 더 compact해지도록 만든다. 6개 benchmark에 대한 종합 실험은 GraphNC가 (1) 서로 다른 GAD 방법의 teacher model 성능을 일관되게 그리고 상당히 향상시키며 (2) 새로운 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성함을 보여준다."},{"id":"61205","en":"Modeling Spectral Energy Shifts in Spatio-Temporal Graph Anomaly Detection","ko":"시공간 Graph Anomaly Detection에서 스펙트럼 에너지 이동 모델링","authors":"Yilin Liu, Hongchao Zhang, Ahmad Taha, Taylor T Johnson, Meiyi Ma","pos":"#2312","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=sgNhWbqXfJ","abs":"<p>Graph anomaly detection methods aim to distinguish anomalous nodes. While prior methods characterize anomalies through increased variation in the spectral energy distributions, they overlook those that result in decreased variation, i.e., camouflaged anomalies that appear normal. We show that this type of anomaly persists across multiple datasets and remains undetectable by existing spectral approaches. To address this limitation, we propose a node-level spectral energy formulation that is fully compatible with message passing and enables the detection of camouflaged anomalies. Building on this formulation, we introduce an energy-aware graph learning framework that models spectral shifts through energy-driven message passing in both static and time-series graphs. Besides, our unified architecture extends to temporal settings without introducing specialized sequence modules, enabling efficient learning under long sliding windows. Extensive experiments on large-scale benchmarks demonstrate the effectiveness and scalability of our approach.</p>","absKo":"<p>Graph anomaly detection 방법은 이상 노드(anomalous node)를 구별하는 것을 목표로 합니다. 기존 방법들은 spectral energy distribution의 증가된 변동을 통해 이상을 특징짓지만, 변동이 감소하는 경우, 즉 정상처럼 보이는 camouflaged anomaly는 간과합니다. 우리는 이러한 유형의 이상이 여러 dataset에 걸쳐 지속적으로 나타나며 기존 spectral 접근으로는 탐지되지 않음을 보입니다. 이 한계를 해결하기 위해, message passing과 완전히 호환되며 camouflaged anomaly의 탐지를 가능하게 하는 node-level spectral energy formulation을 제안합니다. 이를 바탕으로, 정적 graph와 time-series graph 모두에서 energy-driven message passing을 통해 spectral shift를 모델링하는 energy-aware graph learning framework를 도입합니다. 또한, 우리의 통합 아키텍처는 전용 sequence module을 도입하지 않고도 temporal setting으로 확장되며, 긴 sliding window 하에서 효율적인 학습을 가능하게 합니다. 대규모 benchmark에 대한 광범위한 실험은 우리의 접근이 효과적이고 확장 가능함을 입증합니다.</p>"},{"id":"65770","en":"Message Tuning Outshines Graph Prompt Tuning: A Prismatic Space Perspective","ko":"메시지 튜닝이 그래프 프롬프트 튜닝을 능가한다: 프리즘 공간 관점","authors":"Yancheng Chen, Dun Ma, Shuai Zhang, Yang Liu, Xixun Lin, Xiangyu Zhao, Wenguo Yang, Wei Chen, Chuan Zhou","pos":"#2313","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=AJb9PuUibK","abs":"<p>Graph Foundation Models (GFMs), built upon the <em>Pre-training and Adaptation</em> paradigm, have emerged as a research hotspot in graph learning. For GNN-based GFMs, graph prompt tuning has become the prevailing adaptation method for downstream tasks. Although recent methods explain why graph prompt tuning works, how to rigorously measure its adaptation capacity remains an open problem. Addressing this problem is critical for understanding the capability limits of graph prompt tuning and for developing more powerful adaptation methods. In this paper, we propose Prismatic Space Theory (PS-Theory), a novel mathematical framework to quantify the capacity of adaptation methods, while focusing on establishing the upper bound for the adaptation capacity of graph prompt tuning. Building upon the proposed PS-Theory, we further introduce <strong>M</strong>essage <strong>T</strong>uning for <strong>G</strong>FMs (MTG), a lightweight approach that injects a small set of learnable message prototypes into each layer of the GNN backbone to adaptively guide message fusion without updating pre-trained weights. Through our PS-Theory, we prove that the adaptation capacity of MTG can exceed the theoretical upper bound of graph prompt tuning. Extensive experiments demonstrate that MTG consistently outperforms graph prompt baselines across diverse benchmark datasets, providing strong empirical support for our theoretical findings. Our code is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/MTG.</p>"},{"id":"65412","en":"Message Passing on the Edge: Towards Scalable and Expressive GNNs","ko":"엣지에서의 Message Passing: 확장 가능하고 표현력 있는 GNN을 향하여","authors":"Pablo Barcelo, Fabian Jogl, Alexander Kozachinskiy, Matthias Lanzinger, Stefan Neumann, Cristobal Rojas","pos":"#2314","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=DvvEByY0Xa","abs":"<p>Graph neural networks (GNNs) are widely used in graph learning and most architectures propagate information by passing messages between vertices. In this work, we shift our attention to GNNs that perform message passing on <em>edges</em> and introduce EB-1WL, an edge-based color-refinement test, and a corresponding architecture, EB-GNN.  Our EB-GNN architecture is inspired by the classic triangle-counting algorithm of Chiba and Nishizeki and passes messages along edges and triangles.   Our contributions are as follows: 1. Theoretically, we show that EB-1WL is significantly more expressive than 1WL. We provide a complete logical characterization of EB-1WL in first-order logic, along with distinguishability results via homomorphism counting. To the best of our knowledge, EB-GNN has the strongest theoretical expressivity guarantees among edge-based message-passing GNNs in the literature. 2. Unlike many GNN architectures that are more expressive than 1WL, we prove that EB-1WL and EB-GNN admit near-linear time and memory usage on practical graph learning workloads. 3. We show in experiments that EB-GNN is a highly efficient general-purpose architecture: it substantially outperforms simple MPNNs and remains competitive with task-specialized state-of-the-art GNNs at substantially lower computational cost.</p>"},{"id":"65998","en":"MDGMIX: Boundary-Aware Subgraph Mixing for Multi-Domain Graph Pre-Training","ko":"MDGMIX: 다중 도메인 그래프 사전학습을 위한 경계 인식 서브그래프 혼합","authors":"Ziyu Zheng, Yaming Yang, Ziyu Guan, Wei Zhao, Xinyan Huang","pos":"#2315","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=83HqzmZab8","abs":"<p>Multi-domain graph pre-training is a crucial step in constructing foundational graph models with cross-domain generalization capabilities. However, existing methods predominantly rely on jointly training all source domain graphs, resulting in high computational costs. Furthermore, it remains unclear whether all source domain graph data contribute equally to effective transfer. This paper empirically reveals significant data redundancy in multi-domain graph pre-training. Based on this finding, we propose the Multi-domain Graph Pre-training Framework, MDGMIX, which combines boundary-aware subgraph mixing with hierarchical discrimination. By selecting boundary nodes to construct challenging mixed-domain subgraphs, MDGMIX employs coarse-grained domain discrimination and fine-grained domain decomposition losses to decouple shared patterns from domain-specific patterns. During adaptation, MDGMIX employs a lightweight prompt weighting mechanism to transfer source domain knowledge. Extensive experiments demonstrate that MDGMIX consistently outperforms strong baselines in few-shot classification tasks while exhibiting superior time and memory efficiency.</p>"},{"id":"65665","en":"Bridging Structure and Semantics: Uncertainty-Modulated Dual-Path Diffusion for Robust Text-Attributed Graph Learning","ko":"구조와 의미의 연결: 강건한 텍스트 속성 그래프 학습을 위한 불확실성 변조 이중 경로 Diffusion","authors":"Zhizhi Yu, Jiachen Liu, Qingyu Li, Dongxiao He, Di Jin","pos":"#2403","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=BQ9mGItg7m","abs":"<p>Representation learning on text-attributed graphs (TAGs) is crucial for real-world applications, as it enables effective modeling of both rich node semantics and complex graph structure. Nevertheless, this task is intrinsically challenging due to structural–semantic mismatch stemming from divergent modality distributions, as well as dual-source noise inherent in node textual content and graph structure. Existing approaches often enforce a rigid fusion of distinct modalities while overlooking their inherent noise, which inevitably results in persistent distribution gaps and amplifies mixed interference during information propagation. To address these issues, we propose UDPD, an Uncertainty-modulated Dual-Path Diffusion model for robust text-attributed graph learning. Specifically, we first employ a dual-perspective node encoding strategy to separately learn semantic and structural embeddings. We then introduce a cooperative diffusion paradigm with parallel semantic and structural branches, where mutual guidance enables progressive alignment of different distributions while effectively suppressing modality inherent noise. Crucially, the reverse process is guided by node uncertainty, which is used to adaptively modulate cross-branch interaction strength, ensuring robust coupling and maximizing denoising effectiveness. Extensive experiments on five public benchmarks demonstrate the effectiveness and superiority of our UDPD over state-of-the-art baselines.</p>"},{"id":"65733","en":"CELL: A Causal Perspective for Fairness-aware Graph Adaptation","ko":"CELL: 공정성 인식 그래프 적응을 위한 인과적 관점","authors":"Hourun Li, Yifan Wang, Qinghua Ran, Junyu Luo, Jia Yang, Changling Zhou, Zhiping Xiao, Wei Ju, Xiao Luo, Ming Zhang","pos":"#2404","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=AheW1kJ5E9","abs":"<p>This paper investigates fairness-aware graph adaptation, aiming to transfer knowledge from a labeled source graph to an unlabeled target graph while explicitly accounting for fairness.  Most prior methods rely on adversarial learning to learn invariant graph representations of sensitive attributes.  However, these approaches assume that sensitive attributes of the target domain are available, which often fails in real-world deployments.  To address this limitation, we propose \\underline{C}ausality-attended Repres\\underline{e}ntation Dientang\\underline{l}ement with Structural A\\underline{l}ignment (CELL) for fairness-aware graph adaptation without requiring target sensitive labels.  The key idea of CELL is to build a causal graph that captures the underlying graph-generation mechanism and guides representation disentanglement toward improved fairness. In particular, CELL employs a sensitive encoder and a causal encoder to extract sensitive and causal factors respectively.  We encourage disentanglement by minimizing the mutual information between causal and sensitive representations, considering the conditional distribution. To leverage unlabeled target data, we further generate pseudo-labels for both target task labels and sensitive attributes, and use similarity relations to derive unbiased node representations.  Finally, to further mitigate domain shift, we build a fairness-aware bipartite graph that provides additional structural supervision for cross-domain alignment.  Extensive experiments on benchmark datasets demonstrate that CELL consistently outperforms strong baselines in both predictive performance and fairness.</p>"},{"id":"63141","en":"Clustering as Reasoning: A $k$-Means Interpretation of Chain-of-Thought Graph Learning","ko":"추론으로서의 클러스터링: Chain-of-Thought 그래프 학습의 $k$-Means 해석","authors":"Xuanting Xie, Zhaochen Guo, Bingheng Li, Xingtong Yu, Zhifei Liao, zhao kang, Yuan Fang","pos":"#2405","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Zg9rjewo83","abs":"Chain-of-Thought (CoT) prompting has shown promise in enhancing the reasoning capabilities of large language models (LLMs) on text-attributed graphs (TAGs). This work reframes CoT-based graph learning through the principle of clustering as reasoning, offering a $k$-means interpretation of how iterative reasoning operates over graph-structured data. We observe that existing graph CoT methods rely on disjoint architectures and fixed graph representations, limiting step-by-step semantic-topological interaction and interpretability. To overcome this limitation, we propose a unified framework named KCoT that integrates CoT reasoning with graph representation learning. Our key theoretical result reveals a formal mathematical correspondence between a Transformer block and the $k$-means algorithm, allowing reasoning to be interpreted as iterative assignment and update steps. Based on this insight, we introduce a Semantic Discriminating Prompt that explicitly formulates these steps as structured CoT reasoning, together with a structure-grounded alignment strategy to fuse topological priors with evolving thought-conditioned representations. Experiments on standard benchmarks demonstrate consistent improvements over state-of-the-art methods, validating clustering as a principled mechanism for CoT-based graph learning.","absKo":"Chain-of-Thought (CoT) prompting은 text-attributed graphs (TAGs)에서 large language models (LLMs)의 추론 능력을 향상시키는 데 유망함이 입증되었다. 본 연구는 CoT 기반 graph learning을 clustering as reasoning이라는 원리로 재해석하여, 반복적 추론이 graph-structured data 위에서 어떻게 작동하는지에 대한 $k$-means 해석을 제시한다. 우리는 기존 graph CoT 방법들이 분리된 architecture와 고정된 graph representation에 의존하여, 단계별 semantic-topological interaction과 interpretability가 제한된다는 점을 관찰한다. 이러한 한계를 극복하기 위해, 우리는 CoT reasoning과 graph representation learning을 통합한 KCoT라는 통합 framework를 제안한다. 우리의 핵심 이론 결과는 Transformer block과 $k$-means algorithm 사이의 형식적 수학적 대응을 밝혀, reasoning을 반복적인 assignment 및 update step으로 해석할 수 있게 한다. 이 통찰을 바탕으로, 우리는 이러한 단계를 구조화된 CoT reasoning으로 명시적으로 정식화하는 Semantic Discriminating Prompt와 함께, topology prior를 진화하는 thought-conditioned representation과 융합하는 structure-grounded alignment strategy를 도입한다. 표준 benchmark에서의 실험은 state-of-the-art method에 비해 일관된 성능 향상을 보여 주며, clustering이 CoT-based graph learning의 원리적 메커니즘임을 검증한다."},{"id":"66227","en":"ERAlign: Energy-based Representation Alignment of GNNs and LLMs on Text-attributed Graphs","ko":"ERAlign: 텍스트 속성 그래프에서 GNN과 LLM의 에너지 기반 표현 정렬","authors":"Xianlin Zeng, Fan Xia, Xiangyu Chen","pos":"#2406","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=5crqGLOpnf","abs":"<p>Text-attributed Graphs (TAGs) incorporate textual node attributes with graph structures to describe rich relational semantics. Recent efforts to integrate Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) and Large Language Models (LLMs) have shown promise for learning on TAGs, yet achieving well-aligned representations remains challenging. Prior studies largely rely on heuristics that perform coarse-grained matching. They lack sufficient constraints and ignore distributional alignment, leading to representation drift and limited generalization. Building on Energy-based Models (EBMs), we propose an <strong>E</strong>nergy-based <strong>R</strong>epresentation <strong>Align</strong>ment (ERAlign) framework that projects GNN-encoded graph structure and LLM-derived text embeddings in a shared latent space to achieve distribution consistency. Concretely, layer-wise alignment is quantified by a distance metric and optimized via an EBM objective. By decreasing energy values, our framework yields well-aligned representations for downstream tasks. During training, we introduce Energy Discrepancy (ED) to avoid high sampling costs associated with intractable normalization. ED also carries theoretical guarantees of higher training efficiency and reduced energy landscape distortion. Empirical evaluations on eight TAG datasets demonstrate that ERAlign obtains state-of-the-art performance across varying levels of supervision and cross-task transfer scenario.</p>"},{"id":"64137","en":"Generalist Graph Anomaly Detection via Prototype-Based Distillation","ko":"프로토타입 기반 증류를 통한 범용 그래프 이상 탐지","authors":"Yiming Xu, Zihan Chen, Zhen Peng, Song Wang, Bin Shi, Bo Dong, Chao Shen","pos":"#2408","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=QZa5zaj2oP","abs":"<p>Driven by the pressing demand for graph anomaly detection (GAD) in high-stakes domains, the generalist GAD paradigm, which trains a single detector transferable across new graphs, has recently gained growing attention. However, existing methods often rely on scarce and costly annotations for training and sometimes even require few-shot support at inference, which limits their robustness to diverse and unseen anomaly patterns. To address this limitation, we introduce ProMoS, the first unsupervised generalist GAD framework, which detects anomalies by modeling the abundant normality in unlabeled data. ProMoS adopts a knowledge-distillation paradigm to distill normality priors from a frozen self-supervised graph neural network (GNN) teacher to a mixture-of-students model with shared global and lightweight personalized branches, enabling efficient and expressive normality modeling without learning from scratch.  We further propose prototype-guided soft-label distillation to align teacher and student in a shared prototype space, enhancing cross-graph generalizability. During inference, ProMoS performs zero-shot anomaly detection on unseen graphs via distillation bias and prototype geometric deviation. Extensive experiments show the effectiveness and efficiency of ProMoS, charting a practical path toward label-free, zero-shot generalist GAD.</p>","absKo":"<p>고위험 도메인에서 graph anomaly detection(GAD)에 대한 절실한 수요에 힘입어, 단일 detector를 학습해 새로운 graph로 전이 가능한 generalist GAD paradigm이 최근 큰 주목을 받고 있다. 그러나 기존 방법들은 대개 학습을 위해 희소하고 비용이 큰 annotation에 의존하며, 때로는 inference 시 few-shot support까지 요구하므로 다양한 미지의 anomaly pattern에 대한 robustness가 제한된다. 이러한 한계를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 unlabeled data에 풍부하게 존재하는 normality를 modeling하여 anomaly를 탐지하는, 최초의 unsupervised generalist GAD framework인 ProMoS를 제안한다. ProMoS는 knowledge-distillation paradigm을 채택하여, frozen self-supervised graph neural network(GNN) teacher로부터 normality prior를 distill하고, shared global branch와 lightweight personalized branch로 구성된 mixture-of-students model로 이를 전달함으로써, 처음부터 학습하지 않고도 효율적이면서도 표현력이 풍부한 normality modeling을 가능하게 한다. 또한 teacher와 student를 shared prototype space에서 정렬하기 위해 prototype-guided soft-label distillation을 제안하여 cross-graph generalizability를 향상시킨다. inference 단계에서 ProMoS는 distillation bias와 prototype geometric deviation을 통해 보지 못한 graph에서 zero-shot anomaly detection을 수행한다. 광범위한 실험은 ProMoS의 효과성과 효율성을 입증하며, label-free, zero-shot generalist GAD를 향한 실용적인 경로를 제시한다.</p>"},{"id":"61945","en":"Generative Representation Learning on Hyper-relational Knowledge Graphs via Masked Discrete Diffusion","ko":"마스킹된 discrete diffusion 기반 hyper-relational knowledge graph 생성형 표현 학습","authors":"Jaejun Lee, Seheon Kim, Joyce Whang","pos":"#2409","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=lRZmoqiAPg","abs":"<p>Hyper-relational knowledge graphs (HKGs) effectively represent complex facts. While inferring new knowledge in HKGs is a critical problem, current methods cast it as a simple link prediction, assuming that nearly all entities and relations within a fact are known, leaving only a single blank to be filled. However, this restricted assumption may not hold in real-world scenarios in which multiple, or even all, constituent components of a fact may be missing simultaneously. To bridge this gap, we introduce a task called fact generation: generating a valid hyper-relational fact from an arbitrarily masked query, i.e., completing a partially observed fact or generating a fact from scratch. We propose KREPE, the first generative representation learning method for HKGs that learns to model the probability distributions of missing components conditioned on the local fact components and global structure of HKGs via a masked discrete diffusion. KREPE models both the intra-fact dependencies by contextual message passing and inter-fact correlations by aggregating stochastically sampled contexts. KREPE seamlessly unifies link prediction and fact generation within a single training framework, achieving state-of-the-art performance on standard HKG link prediction benchmarks and outperforming LLM-based baselines in generating novel and correct facts.</p>","absKo":"<p>Hyper-relational knowledge graph(HKG)는 복잡한 fact를 효과적으로 표현한다. HKG에서 새로운 knowledge를 추론하는 것은 중요한 문제이지만, 현재 방법들은 이를 단순한 link prediction으로 간주하여, fact 내의 거의 모든 entity와 relation이 알려져 있고 단 하나의 빈칸만 채우면 된다고 가정한다. 그러나 이러한 제한된 가정은 하나의 fact를 구성하는 여러 요소, 심지어 모든 요소가 동시에 누락될 수 있는 실제 시나리오에서는 성립하지 않을 수 있다. 이 간극을 메우기 위해, 우리는 fact generation이라는 태스크를 도입한다. 이는 임의로 mask된 query로부터 유효한 hyper-relational fact를 생성하는 것으로, 부분적으로 관측된 fact를 완성하거나 fact를 처음부터 생성하는 것을 의미한다. 우리는 KREPE를 제안하는데, 이는 masked discrete diffusion을 통해 local fact component와 HKG의 global structure에 조건부인 missing component의 probability distribution을 학습하는 HKG를 위한 첫 번째 generative representation learning method이다. KREPE는 contextual message passing으로 fact 내부 의존성을, stochastically sampled context를 aggregation함으로써 fact 간 상관관계를 모두 모델링한다. KREPE는 단일 training framework 안에서 link prediction과 fact generation을 매끄럽게 통합하며, 표준 HKG link prediction benchmark에서 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성하고, 새로운 정확한 fact를 생성하는 데서는 LLM-based baseline을 능가한다.</p>"},{"id":"65744","en":"Graph-GRPO: Training Graph Flow Models with Reinforcement Learning","ko":"Graph-GRPO: 강화학습을 통한 Graph Flow 모델 학습","authors":"Baoheng Zhu, Deyu Bo, Delvin Zhang, Xiao Wang","pos":"#2410","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Abko94Sl7D","abs":"<p>Graph generation is a fundamental task with broad applications, such as drug discovery. Recently, discrete flow matching-based graph generation, \\aka, graph flow model (GFM), has emerged due to its superior performance and flexible sampling. However, effectively aligning GFMs with complex human preferences or task-specific objectives remains a significant challenge. In this paper, we propose Graph-GRPO, an online reinforcement learning (RL) framework for training GFMs under verifiable rewards. Our method makes two key contributions: (1) We derive an analytical expression for the transition probability of GFMs, replacing the Monte Carlo sampling and enabling fully differentiable rollouts for RL training; (2) We propose a refinement strategy that randomly perturbs specific nodes and edges in a graph, and regenerates them, allowing for localized exploration and self-improvement of generation quality. Extensive experiments on both synthetic and real datasets demonstrate the effectiveness of Graph-GRPO. With only 50 denoising steps, our method achieves 95.0\\% and 97.5\\% Valid-Unique-Novelty scores on the planar and tree datasets, respectively. Moreover, Graph-GRPO achieves state-of-the-art performance on the molecular optimization tasks, outperforming graph-based and fragment-based RL methods as well as classic genetic algorithms.</p>"},{"id":"61582","en":"InvGNN: Learning Invertible Node Representations on Graphs","ko":"InvGNN: Graph에서 Invertible Node Representation 학습","authors":"Giannis Nikolentzos, Dimitrios Kelesis, Nikolaos Nakis","pos":"#2412","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=okKDijCwRn","abs":"<p>Over the past decade, Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) have become a standard tool for solving machine learning problems on graphs. While many aspects of GNNs have been studied in depth, including their efficiency and expressive power, the invertibility of these models has remained largely unexplored. Standard aggregation functions, such as the mean, max and sum operators, are not invertible, which limits their applicability in tasks requiring invertible transformations. In this work, we introduce an invertible GNN layer. By stacking multiple such layers, we construct fully invertible GNN models, which we refer to as InvGNNs. These models inherit the benefits of invertible neural networks, including low memory usage for deep architectures, exact likelihood computation, and generative modeling capabilities. We demonstrate that InvGNNs can match the expressive power of the 1-dimensional Weisfeiler-Leman algorithm, showing that invertibility does not compromise model expressiveness. On standard graph classification benchmarks, our model performs comparably to other well-established GNNs, such as GIN. Beyond classification, we demonstrate the potential of invertible layers through density estimation tasks, including outlier detection and node feature generation. Our experiments confirm that InvGNNs effectively handle tasks that benefit from invertible layers.</p>","absKo":"<p>지난 10년 동안 Graph Neural Networks (GNNs)는 그래프에서 machine learning 문제를 해결하기 위한 표준 도구가 되었다. GNN의 효율성과 표현력 등 여러 측면은 깊이 연구되어 왔지만, 이들 모델의 invertibility는 대부분 아직 탐구되지 않았다. mean, max, sum 연산자와 같은 표준 aggregation function은 invertible하지 않기 때문에, invertible transformation이 필요한 task에 적용하는 데 한계가 있다. 본 연구에서는 invertible GNN layer를 제안한다. 이러한 layer를 여러 개 쌓아 fully invertible GNN model을 구성하며, 이를 InvGNNs라고 부른다. 이 모델은 deep architecture에서 낮은 memory usage, exact likelihood computation, generative modeling capability를 포함한 invertible neural network의 장점을 계승한다. 우리는 InvGNNs가 1-dimensional Weisfeiler-Leman algorithm과 같은 수준의 expressive power를 보일 수 있음을 보이며, invertibility가 model expressiveness를 저해하지 않음을 보여준다. 표준 graph classification benchmark에서 우리 모델은 GIN과 같은 다른 well-established GNN과 비슷한 성능을 보인다. classification을 넘어, outlier detection과 node feature generation을 포함한 density estimation task를 통해 invertible layer의 잠재력을 입증한다. 우리의 실험은 InvGNNs가 invertible layer의 이점을 얻는 task를 효과적으로 처리함을 확인한다.</p>"},{"id":"62088","en":"A Graph Foundation Model with Cross-Modal  Alignment and Modality-Aware Expert Fusion for Multi-Modal Graphs","ko":"멀티모달 그래프를 위한 Cross-Modal Alignment와 Modality-Aware Expert Fusion 기반 그래프 Foundation Model","authors":"Dongxiao He, AnKang Yang, Jitao Zhao, Di Jin","pos":"#3404","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=jwAnxpqHHX","abs":"<p>Graph Foundation Models (GFMs) aim to learn universal patterns through large-scale pretraining on diverse graphs and generalize to open-world scenarios. While GFMs have garnered significant attention, existing works primarily focus on sigle-modal graphs. However, many real-world graphs are multimodal, consisting of structures alongside diverse features derived from modalities such as text and images. To date, exploration into Multimodal Graph Foundation Models (MGFMs) remains limited. Incorporating multimodal data provides a more comprehensive view, allowing models to learn richer semantics, thereby advancing GFMs. We are therefore motivated to explore MGFMs, where the core challenge lies in synergistically encoding structures and multimodal features to achieve effective cross-modal alignment and fusion. To this end, we propose a graph foundation model with Cross-modal Alignment and Modality-aware Expert fusion, CAME. Specifically, CAME first generates graph embeddings for each individual modality. We then introduce a multimodal multi-expert encoding mechanism, which includes a dimension-wise routing strategy to fuse multimodal information. Finally, we employ a cross-modal contrastive loss to train CAME, enabling the adaptive alignment and fusion across different modalities. Extensive experiments demonstrate the effectiveness of CAME across multiple tasks and diverse multimodal graph datasets.</p>","absKo":"<p>Graph Foundation Models (GFMs)은 다양한 graph에 대한 대규모 pretraining을 통해 보편적 패턴을 학습하고 open-world scenario로 일반화하는 것을 목표로 한다. GFMs는 큰 주목을 받아왔지만, 기존 연구는 주로 single-modal graph에 초점을 맞추고 있다. 그러나 많은 실제 graph는 text와 image 같은 modality에서 유래한 다양한 feature와 함께 structure를 포함하는 multimodal graph이다. 현재까지 Multimodal Graph Foundation Models (MGFMs)에 대한 탐구는 제한적이다. multimodal data를 통합하면 더 포괄적인 관점을 제공하여 모델이 더 풍부한 semantic을 학습하게 되고, 이는 GFMs의 발전으로 이어진다. 따라서 우리는 MGFMs를 탐구하고자 하며, 핵심 과제는 structure와 multimodal feature를 시너지 있게 encoding하여 효과적인 cross-modal alignment와 fusion을 달성하는 데 있다. 이를 위해 우리는 Cross-modal Alignment와 Modality-aware Expert fusion을 갖춘 graph foundation model인 CAME를 제안한다. 구체적으로, CAME는 먼저 각 개별 modality에 대한 graph embedding을 생성한다. 그런 다음 multimodal 정보를 통합하기 위해 dimension-wise routing strategy를 포함하는 multimodal multi-expert encoding mechanism을 도입한다. 마지막으로 cross-modal contrastive loss를 사용해 CAME를 학습함으로써 서로 다른 modality 간 adaptive alignment와 fusion을 가능하게 한다. 광범위한 실험은 여러 task와 다양한 multimodal graph dataset에서 CAME의 효과를 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"62615","en":"Learning Discriminative and Generalizable Anomaly Detector for Dynamic Graph with Limited Supervision","ko":"제한된 Supervision에서 Dynamic Graph를 위한 판별적·일반화 가능한 Anomaly Detector 학습","authors":"Yuxing Tian, Yiyan Qi, Fengran Mo, Weixu Zhang, Jian Guo, Jian-Yun Nie","pos":"#3613","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=f1C38SmxkP","abs":"<p>Dynamic graph anomaly detection (DGAD) is critical for many real-world applications but remains challenging due to the scarcity of labeled anomalies. Existing methods are either unsupervised or semi-supervised:  unsupervised methods avoid the need for labeled anomalies but often produce ambiguous boundary, whereas semi-supervised methods can overfit to the limited labeled anomalies and generalize poorly to unseen anomalies. To address this gap, we consider a largely underexplored problem in DGAD: learning a discriminative boundary from normal/unlabeled data, while leveraging limited labeled anomalies \\textbf{when available} without sacrificing generalization to unseen anomalies. To this end, we propose an effective, generalizable, and model-agnostic framework with three main components: (i) residual representation encoding that capture deviations between current interactions and their historical context, providing anomaly-relevant signals; (ii) a restriction loss that constrain the normal representations within an interval bounded by two co-centered hyperspheres, ensuring consistent scales while keeping anomalies separable; (iii) a bi-boundary optimization strategy that learns a discriminative and robust boundary using the normal log-likelihood distribution modeled by a normalizing flow. Extensive experiments demonstrate the superiority of our framework across diverse evaluation settings.</p>","absKo":"<p>Dynamic graph anomaly detection(DGAD)은 많은 실제 응용에서 매우 중요하지만, labeled anomaly의 부족 때문에 여전히 어렵다. 기존 방법은 unsupervised 또는 semi-supervised로 나뉜다. unsupervised 방법은 labeled anomaly가 필요 없지만 종종 모호한 boundary를 만들고, semi-supervised 방법은 제한된 labeled anomaly에 과적합되어 보지 못한 anomaly에 일반화가 잘 되지 않는다. 이 간극을 메우기 위해, 우리는 DGAD에서 비교적 충분히 탐구되지 않은 문제를 고려한다. 즉, normal/unlabeled data로부터 판별적인 boundary를 학습하면서, \\textbf{가능한 경우} 제한된 labeled anomaly를 활용하되 보지 못한 anomaly에 대한 일반화는 희생하지 않는 것이다. 이를 위해 우리는 세 가지 주요 구성요소를 갖는 효과적이고 일반화 가능하며 model-agnostic한 framework를 제안한다. (i) 현재 interaction과 그 historical context 사이의 편차를 포착하여 anomaly 관련 신호를 제공하는 residual representation encoding, (ii) anomaly를 분리 가능하게 유지하면서 일관된 scale을 보장하도록 두 개의 동심 hypersphere로 둘러싸인 구간 안에 normal representation을 제약하는 restriction loss, (iii) normalizing flow로 모델링한 normal log-likelihood distribution을 사용하여 판별적이고 견고한 boundary를 학습하는 bi-boundary optimization strategy. 광범위한 실험은 다양한 평가 설정에서 우리의 framework가 우수함을 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"65594","en":"CCLRec: Consensus-driven Contrastive Learning for LLM-enhanced Graph Recommendation","ko":"CCLRec: LLM 강화 그래프 추천을 위한 합의 기반 대조 학습","authors":"Ting Guo, Dongyu Pei, Litiao Qiu, Xiaoying Liao, KE LIANG, Peng Song, Pinle Qin","pos":"#4005","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=C2i7ciwxKQ","abs":"<p>Recommendation systems seek to accurately model user preferences from a large set of candidate items. Graph neural networks (GNNs) have emerged as a dominant approach in this domain due to their ability to capture high-order user–item interactions. Recent efforts have aimed to enhance GNN-based representation learning by incorporating the semantic reasoning capabilities of large language models (LLMs). However, existing methods often process graph structural information and LLM-derived semantic knowledge separately, creating a supervisory gap between structural proximity and semantic relevance. To bridge this gap, we propose CCLRec, a consensus-driven contrastive learning framework for recommendation. CCLRec deeply integrates structural and semantic information by identifying consistent signals. Specifically, we first use an LLM to extract semantic representations of items and to sample candidate positive/negative sets in the semantic space. We then introduce a structural–semantic consensus mining strategy that computes the intersection between a node’s structural neighbors in the graph and its semantically similar items. This allows us to identify high-confidence positive pairs endorsed by both collaborative filtering patterns and LLM-based reasoning. By centering contrastive learning on these consensus pairs and applying a weight-aware reinforcement mechanism during training, CCLRec significantly amplifies the contribution of high-quality consensus features during training. Experiments across multiple public benchmarks show that CCLRec consistently outperforms state-of-the-art methods on key metrics, demonstrating the effectiveness of our consensus-aware design.</p>"},{"id":"65791","en":"MASPOB: Bandit-Based Prompt Optimization for Multi-Agent Systems with Graph Neural Networks","ko":"MASPOB: Graph Neural Network를 활용한 멀티에이전트 시스템을 위한 밴딧 기반 프롬프트 최적화","authors":"Zhi Hong, Qian Zhang, Jiahang Sun, Zhiwei Shang, Mingze Kong, Xiangyi Wang, Yao Shu, Zhongxiang Dai","pos":"#1916","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=A5venxSvpw","abs":"<p>Large Language Models (LLMs) have achieved significant success across a wide range of tasks, serving as the cognitive backbone for Multi-Agent Systems (MAS) designed to orchestrate complex practical workflows. Given that MAS performance is highly sensitive to input prompts and many deployment scenarios preclude MAS architecture modifications, prompt optimization emerges as a critical strategy for performance enhancement. However, real-world deployment is impeded by three key challenges: (1) the need for high sample efficiency due to prohibitive evaluation costs, (2) topology-induced coupling among prompts, and (3) the combinatorial explosion of the search space. To address these challenges, we introduce <strong>MASPOB</strong> (<strong>M</strong>ulti-<strong>A</strong>gent <strong>S</strong>ystem <strong>P</strong>rompt <strong>O</strong>ptimization via <strong>B</strong>andits), a novel sample-efficient framework based on bandits. By leveraging Upper Confidence Bound (UCB) to quantify uncertainty, the bandit framework balances exploration and exploitation, maximizing gains within a strictly limited budget. To handle topology-induced coupling, MASPOB integrates Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) to capture structural priors, learning topology-aware representations of prompt semantics. Furthermore, it employs coordinate ascent to decompose the optimization into univariate sub-problems, reducing search complexity from exponential to linear. Extensive experiments across diverse benchmarks demonstrate that MASPOB achieves state-of-the-art performance, consistently outperforming existing baselines.</p>"},{"id":"65352","en":"WebWorld: A Large-Scale World Model for Web Agent Training","ko":"WebWorld: Web 에이전트 학습을 위한 대규모 World Model","authors":"Zikai Xiao, Jianhong Tu, Chuhang Zou, Yuxin Zuo, Zhi Li, Peng Wang, Bowen Yu, Fei Huang, Junyang Lin, Zuozhu Liu","pos":"#2117","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ES7Vy9rvRl","abs":"<p>Web agents require massive trajectories to generalize, yet real-world training is constrained by network latency, rate limits, and safety risks. We introduce \\textbf{WebWorld} series, the first open-web simulator trained at scale. While existing simulators are restricted to closed environments with thousands of trajectories, WebWorld leverages a scalable data pipeline to train on 1M+ open-web interactions, supporting reasoning, multi-format data, and long-horizon simulations of 30+ steps. For intrinsic evaluation, we introduce WebWorld-Bench with dual metrics spanning nine dimensions, where WebWorld achieves simulation performance comparable to Gemini-3-Pro. For extrinsic evaluation, Qwen3-14B trained on WebWorld-synthesized trajectories improves by +9.2\\% on WebArena, reaching performance comparable to GPT-4o. WebWorld enables effective inference-time search, outperforming GPT-5 as a world model. Beyond web simulation, WebWorld exhibits cross-domain generalization to code, GUI, and game environments, providing a replicable recipe for world-model construction.</p>"},{"id":"65501","en":"Agent Primitives: Reuseable Latent Building Blocks for Multi-Agent Systems","ko":"Agent Primitives: 멀티 에이전트 시스템을 위한 재사용 가능한 잠재 구성 블록","authors":"Haibo Jin, Peng Kuang, Ye Yu, Xiaopeng Yuan, Haohan Wang","pos":"#117","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=CzShhpY2qU","abs":"While existing multi-agent systems (MAS) can handle complex problems by enabling collaboration among multiple agents, they are often highly task-specific, relying on manually crafted agent roles and interaction prompts, which leads to increased architectural complexity and limited reusability across tasks. Moreover, most MAS communicate primarily through natural language, making them vulnerable to error accumulation and instability in long-context, multi-stage interactions within internal agent histories.  In this work, we propose \\textbf{Agent Primitives}, a set of reusable latent building blocks for LLM-based MAS. Inspired by neural network design, where complex models are built from reusable components, we observe that many existing MAS architectures can be decomposed into a small number of recurring internal computation patterns. Based on this observation, we instantiate three primitives: Review, Voting and Selection, and Planning and Execution. All primitives communicate internally via key–value (KV) cache, which improves both robustness and efficiency by mitigating information degradation across multi-stage interactions. To enable automatic system construction, an Organizer agent selects and composes primitives for each query, guided by a lightweight knowledge pool of previously successful configurations, forming a primitive-based MAS.  Experiments show that primitives-based MAS improve average accuracy by 12.0–16.5\\% over single-agent baselines, reduce token usage and inference latency by approximately 3$\\times$–4$\\times$ compared to text-based MAS, while incurring only 1.3$\\times$–1.6$\\times$ overhead relative to single-agent inference and providing more stable performance across model backbones."},{"id":"63915","en":"Training with Honeypots: Reshaping How LLMs Fail","ko":"Honeypot으로 학습하기: LLM의 실패 방식을 재구성하기","authors":"Samuel Simko, Punya Pandey, Zhijing Jin, Bernhard Schölkopf","pos":"#1601","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=SaSbv33Mem","abs":"<p>Automated red-teaming of Large Language Models (LLMs) commonly relies on attack success rates (ASR) as a proxy for real-world harm, implicitly assuming that judge-detected violations correspond to actionable risk. In practice, safety judges are imperfect, and outputs that satisfy automated criteria for harm can vary widely in their operational usefulness. In this work, we investigate whether model failure modes can be reshaped so that, when defenses fail, they preferentially produce low-utility, non-actionable outputs rather than highly actionable harm. Inspired by honeypots in computer security, we construct responses that are frequently flagged as harmful by automated judges yet provide little real-world operational value, and treat them as hard negatives in the safety training pipeline. Our findings show that shaping how models fail under attack can improve overall safety by reducing both the real-world impact and the frequency of harmful failures, and serves as a practical complement to ASR-based evaluations.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large Language Models (LLMs)의 automated red-teaming은 실제 피해의 대리 지표로 attack success rate (ASR)에 주로 의존하며, 자동 판정된 위반이 실행 가능한 위험에 대응한다는 가정을 암묵적으로 둡니다. 실제로 safety judge는 완벽하지 않으며, harm에 대한 자동 기준을 만족하는 출력도 operational usefulness는 매우 다양할 수 있습니다. 본 연구에서는 방어가 실패했을 때, 모델 failure mode를 조정하여 높은 실행 가능성을 지닌 harm보다 낮은 utility의 non-actionable output을 우선적으로 생성하도록 할 수 있는지 살펴봅니다. computer security의 honeypot에서 영감을 받아, 자동 judge에는 자주 harmful로 표시되지만 실제 운영상 가치는 거의 없는 response를 구성하고 이를 safety training pipeline에서 hard negative로 취급합니다. 우리의 결과는 공격 하에서 모델이 실패하는 방식을 shaping하는 것이 실제 세계의 영향과 harmful failure의 빈도를 모두 줄여 전체 안전성을 향상시킬 수 있으며, ASR 기반 평가를 보완하는 실용적 방법임을 보여줍니다.</p>"},{"id":"61062","en":"What Do Agents Learn from Trajectory-SFT: Semantics or Interfaces?","ko":"Agent는 Trajectory-SFT에서 무엇을 배우는가: 의미인가 인터페이스인가?","authors":"Weizheng Gu, Chengze Li, Zhuohao Yu, Mengyuan Sun, Zhibang Yang, Wei Wang, Hongrui Jia, Shikun Zhang, Wei Ye","pos":"#1609","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=u1i3XoSXQG","abs":"<p>Large language models are increasingly evaluated as interactive agents, yet standard agent benchmarks conflate two qualitatively distinct sources of success: semantic tool-use and interface-specific interaction pattern memorization. Because both mechanisms can yield identical task success on the original interface, benchmark scores alone are not identifiable evidence of environment-invariant capability. We propose <strong>PIPE</strong>, a protocol-level evaluation augmentation for diagnosing interface reliance by minimally rewriting environment interfaces while preserving task semantics and execution behavior. Across 16 environments from AgentBench and AgentGym and a range of open-source and API-based agents, PIPE reveals that trajectory-SFT substantially amplifies interface shortcutting: trained agents degrade sharply under minimal interface rewrites, while non-trajectory-trained models remain largely stable. We further introduce Interface Reliance (IR), a counterbalanced alias-based metric that quantifies preference for training-time interfaces, and show that interface shortcutting exhibits environment-dependent, non-monotonic training dynamics that remain invisible under standard evaluation. Our code is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/What-Do-Agents-Learn-from-Trajectory-SFT-Semantics-or-Interfaces--0831/.</p>","absKo":"대규모 언어 모델은 점점 interactive agent로 평가되고 있지만, 표준 agent benchmark는 성공의 두 질적으로 다른 원인, 즉 semantic tool-use와 interface-specific interaction pattern memorization을 혼동한다. 두 메커니즘 모두 원래 interface에서 동일한 task success를 만들어낼 수 있으므로, benchmark 점수만으로는 environment-invariant capability의 증거가 될 수 없다. 우리는 task semantics와 execution behavior를 보존하면서 environment interface를 최소한으로 다시 작성하여 interface 의존성을 진단하는 protocol-level evaluation augmentation인 <strong>PIPE</strong>를 제안한다. AgentBench와 AgentGym의 16개 environment, 그리고 다양한 open-source 및 API-based agent 전반에서 PIPE는 trajectory-SFT가 interface shortcutting을 크게 증폭시킨다는 사실을 드러낸다. 즉, trajectory로 학습된 agent는 최소한의 interface rewrite에도 급격히 성능이 저하되는 반면, trajectory로 학습되지 않은 model은 대체로 안정적으로 유지된다. 우리는 또한 training-time interface에 대한 선호를 정량화하는 counterbalanced alias-based metric인 Interface Reliance (IR)를 도입하고, interface shortcutting이 standard evaluation에서는 보이지 않는 environment-dependent한 비단조적 training dynamics를 보인다는 점을 제시한다. 우리의 code는 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/What-Do-Agents-Learn-from-Trajectory-SFT-Semantics-or-Interfaces--0831/ 에서 उपलब्ध하다.</p>"},{"id":"65129","en":"Which LLM Multi-Agent Protocol to Choose?","ko":"어떤 LLM 멀티 에이전트 프로토콜을 선택할 것인가?","authors":"Hongyi Du, Jiaqi Su, Jisen Li, Lijie Ding, Yingxuan Yang, Peixuan Han, Robert Tang, Kunlun Zhu, Jiaxuan You","pos":"#1611","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=GZRiXE2zBe","abs":"<p>As large-scale multi-agent systems evolve, the communication protocol layer has become a critical, yet understudied, component affecting system performance and reliability. Despite a range of protocols, such as JSON-RPC, A2A, ANP, and ACP, protocol selection remains ad hoc. To address this, we introduce ProtocolBench, a benchmark designed to evaluate agent communication protocols across task utility, communication overhead, system performance, and resilience under failure. ProtocolBench uses a three-layer architecture with protocol adapters for fair com- parison, diverse scenarios (e.g., document aggregation, collaborative coding), and detailed telemetry. Our results show protocol choice can impact task completion time by up to 36%, communication overhead by 3.5 seconds, and resilience with statistically observable differences. We also propose ProtocolRouter, a learnable protocol routing system that dynamically selects protocols based on runtime con- ditions, improving performance by up to 18% compared to individual protocols. Our findings highlight that hybrid protocol deployments outperform homogeneous ones by approximately 6.6%, with negligible protocol translation overhead. We release ProtocolBench as an open-source framework to standardize protocol evaluation and improve multi-agent system reliability at scale.</p>"},{"id":"63031","en":"Rule2DRC: Benchmarking LLM Agents for DRC Script Synthesis with Execution-Guided Test Generation","ko":"Rule2DRC: 실행 유도 테스트 생성을 통한 DRC 스크립트 합성용 LLM 에이전트 벤치마킹","authors":"Jinuk Kim, Junsoo Byun, Donghwi Hwang, Seong-Jin Park, Hyun Oh Song","pos":"#1715","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=alXhEw7Ogt","abs":"<p>Manufacturable chip layouts must satisfy thousands of geometry-based design rules, and design rule checking (DRC) enforces them by running executable DRC scripts on layouts. Translating natural language rules into correct DRC scripts is labor-intensive and requires specialized expertise, motivating LLM agents for DRC script synthesis and debugging. However, existing benchmarks have small evaluation sets and often evaluate scripts by code similarity rather than execution correctness, and prior machine learning-based methods either ignore execution feedback or require labeled test layouts as agent's input. To this end, we introduce Rule2DRC, a large-scale benchmark for DRC script coding agents with 1,000 rule-to-script tasks and 13,921 evaluation chip layouts for execution-based scoring. Rule2DRC provides an evaluation pipeline that measures functional correctness via DRC execution outcomes without requiring evaluation layouts as input to the agent. We also propose SplitTester, a tester agent for program selection that uses execution feedback to generate discriminative test cases and separate previously indistinguishable candidate scripts, substantially improving Best-of-N selection performance in this domain.</p>","absKo":"<p>제조 가능한 chip layout은 수천 개의 geometry-based design rule을 만족해야 하며, design rule checking(DRC)은 layout 위에서 실행 가능한 DRC script를 실행함으로써 이를 강제한다. 자연어 규칙을 올바른 DRC script로 변환하는 일은 노동 집약적이며 전문 지식을 요구하므로, DRC script 합성과 디버깅을 위한 LLM agent의 필요성이 커지고 있다. 그러나 기존 benchmark는 평가 집합이 작고, 코드 유사도보다 실행 정당성으로 script를 평가하지 않는 경우가 많으며, 이전의 machine learning 기반 방법은 실행 피드백을 무시하거나 label이 붙은 test layout을 agent 입력으로 요구한다. 이에 우리는 Rule2DRC를 소개한다. 이는 1,000개의 rule-to-script task와 실행 기반 scoring을 위한 13,921개의 평가용 chip layout을 포함하는 대규모 DRC script coding agent benchmark다. Rule2DRC는 평가 layout을 agent 입력으로 요구하지 않으면서 DRC 실행 결과를 통해 functional correctness를 측정하는 평가 pipeline을 제공한다. 또한 우리는 program selection을 위한 tester agent인 SplitTester를 제안한다. 이 agent는 실행 피드백을 사용해 판별적인 test case를 생성하고, 이전에는 구분이 불가능했던 후보 script를 분리함으로써 이 도메인에서 Best-of-N selection 성능을 크게 향상시킨다.</p>"},{"id":"62240","en":"Revisiting Efficiency–Accuracy Scaling in Mixture-of-Experts Architectures","ko":"Mixture-of-Experts 아키텍처에서 효율성–정확도 스케일링의 재고찰","authors":"Venmugil Elango, Nidhi Bhatia, Roger Waleffe, Rasoul Shafipour, Tomer Asida, Abhinav Khattar, Nave Assaf, Maximilian Golub, Joseph Guman, Tiyasa Mitra, Ritchie Zhao, Ritika Borkar, Ran Zilberstein, Mostofa Patwary, Mohammad Shoeybi, Bita Darvish Rouhani","pos":"#1716","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=iQRy0io4sb","abs":"<p>Mixture-of-Experts (MoEs) have become a central component of many state-of-the-art open-source and proprietary large language models. Despite their widespread adoption, it remains unclear how close existing MoE architectures are to optimal with respect to inference cost, as measured by accuracy per floating-point operation and per parameter. In this work, we revisit MoE design from a hardware-software co-design perspective, grounded in empirical and theoretical considerations. We characterize key performance bottlenecks across diverse deployment regimes, spanning offline high-throughput execution and online, latency-critical inference. Guided by these insights, we introduce LatentMoE, a new model architecture resulting from systematic design exploration and optimized for maximized accuracy per unit of compute. Empirical design space exploration at scales of up to 95B parameters and over a 1T-token training horizon, together with supporting theoretical analysis, show that LatentMoE consistently outperforms standard MoE architectures in terms of accuracy per FLOP and per parameter.</p>","absKo":"<p>Mixture-of-Experts (MoE)는 많은 state-of-the-art open-source 및 proprietary large language model의 핵심 구성 요소가 되었다. 널리 채택되었음에도 불구하고, inference cost 측면에서 기존 MoE architecture가 얼마나 optimal에 가까운지는 여전히 분명하지 않다. 여기서 cost는 floating-point operation당 정확도와 parameter당 정확도로 측정된다. 본 연구에서는 empirical 및 theoretical consideration에 기반한 hardware-software co-design 관점에서 MoE design을 다시 살펴본다. 우리는 offline high-throughput execution과 online, latency-critical inference를 아우르는 다양한 deployment regime 전반의 핵심 performance bottleneck을 특성화한다. 이러한 통찰에 따라 우리는 systematic design exploration의 결과로 도출된 새로운 model architecture인 LatentMoE를 제안하며, compute unit당 최대 정확도를 목표로 최적화하였다. 최대 95B parameter 규모와 1T-token 이상의 training horizon에 걸친 empirical design space exploration과 이를 뒷받침하는 theoretical analysis는 LatentMoE가 accuracy per FLOP 및 per parameter 측면에서 standard MoE architecture보다 일관되게 우수함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"65447","en":"R-Diverse: Mitigating Diversity Illusion in Self-Play LLM Training","ko":"R-Diverse: Self-Play LLM 학습에서 다양성 환상 완화","authors":"Gengsheng Li, Jinghan He, Shijie Wang, Dan Zhang, Ruiqi Liu, Renrui Zhang, Zijun Yao, Junfeng Fang, Haiyun Guo, Jinqiao Wang","pos":"#1804","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=DZiuKVvrJW","abs":"<p>Self-play bootstraps LLM reasoning through an iterative Challenger–Solver loop: the Challenger is trained to generate questions that target the Solver's capabilities, and the Solver is optimized on the generated data to expand its reasoning skills. However, existing frameworks like R-Zero often exhibit non-sustained improvement, where early gains degrade as self-play continues. We identify a key failure mode, Diversity Illusion, where the Solver's training signals appear diverse yet collapse into recurring underlying patterns. It manifests as (1) Local Diversity Illusion, where diversity is enforced only within-batch, inducing cross-iteration mode cycling; and (2) Surface Diversity Illusion, where questions vary superficially but require near-identical reasoning skills. To mitigate them, we propose R-Diverse with two aligned innovations: Memory-Augmented Penalty (MAP), which uses a persistent memory bank to discourage recycling across iterations, and Skill-Aware Measurement (SAM), which evaluates diversity by the reasoning skills exercised rather than surface variation of questions. Across 10 math and general reasoning benchmarks, R-Diverse sustains gains over more iterations and consistently outperforms prior self-play methods.</p>"},{"id":"65087","en":"RADAR: Redundancy-Aware Diffusion for Multi-Agent Communication Structure Generation","ko":"RADAR: 멀티 에이전트 통신 구조 생성을 위한 중복 인지 Diffusion","authors":"Zhen Zhang, Wanjing Zhou, Juncheng Li, Hao Fei, Jun Wen, Wei Ji","pos":"#1805","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=GtpiqFaJtZ","abs":"<p>Compared with individual agents, large language model based multi-agent systems have demonstrated great capabilities across a wide range of tasks, including code generation, mathematical reasoning, and planning, etc. Despite their impressive performance, the effectiveness and robustness of these systems heavily rely on their communication topology, which is often fixed or generated in a single step. This restricts fine-grained structural exploration and flexible composition, leading to excessive token consumption for simple tasks or performance bottlenecks for complicated ones. To address this challenge, we introduce RADAR, a redundancy-aware and query-adaptive generative framework that actively reduce communication overhead. Inspired by conditional discrete graph diffusion models, we formulate communication topology synthesis as a step-by-step generation process, guided by the effective size of the graph. Comprehensive experiments on six benchmarks demonstrate that RADAR consistently outperforms recent baselines, achieving higher accuracy, lower token consumption, and greater robustness across diverse scenarios. Our source code and data are available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/RADAR-8430.</p>"},{"id":"63622","en":"Recognize Your Orchestrator: An Entropy Dynamics Perspective for LLM Multi-Agent Systems","ko":"자신의 orchestrator를 인식하라: LLM 멀티에이전트 시스템의 엔트로피 동역학 관점","authors":"Junze Zhu, Weihao Chen, Xuanwang Zhang, Zhen Wu, Xinyu Dai","pos":"#1815","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=VMMQj6M94x","abs":"<p>The transition from single-turn models to Multi-Agent Systems (MAS) promises enhanced problem-solving capabilities, yet the centralized orchestration topology remains a critical point of fragility. To analyze this, we propose a Mean-Field Entropy Dynamics framework, modeling the orchestration process as a system governed by the competing forces of task resolution and cumulative context loading. To facilitate high-resolution validation, we introduce Inverse Workflow Generation (IWG), a multi-agent pipeline that synthesizes process-verifiable, high-complexity benchmarks with dense intermediate checkpoints. We demonstrate that our entropy dynamics model fits empirical trajectories, providing physically interpretable parameters that quantify system stability and performance collapse. Crucially, our analysis uncovers a ``Reasoning Trap\":  while reasoning-heavy models excel in isolated tasks, they frequently fail as orchestrators due to context squeezing. By elucidating the physical mechanisms underlying the Orchestrator and quantifying systemic uncertainty, our findings offer insights for the architectural design development of Multi-Agent Systems in prospective research.</p>","absKo":"<p>single-turn 모델에서 Multi-Agent Systems (MAS)로의 전환은 문제 해결 능력의 향상을 약속하지만, 중앙집중식 orchestration topology는 여전히 중요한 취약점으로 남아 있다. 이를 분석하기 위해 우리는 Mean-Field Entropy Dynamics framework를 제안하며, orchestration 과정을 task resolution과 cumulative context loading이 서로 경쟁하는 힘에 의해 지배되는 시스템으로 모델링한다. 고해상도 검증을 가능하게 하기 위해, 우리는 process-verifiable하고 high-complexity인 benchmark를 dense intermediate checkpoint와 함께 합성하는 multi-agent pipeline인 Inverse Workflow Generation (IWG)를 도입한다. 우리는 우리의 entropy dynamics model이 경험적 trajectory에 잘 맞으며, system stability와 performance collapse를 정량화하는 물리적으로 해석 가능한 parameter를 제공함을 보인다. 특히 우리의 분석은 ``Reasoning Trap''을 밝혀낸다. 즉, reasoning-heavy 모델은 고립된 task에서는 뛰어나지만, context squeezing 때문에 orchestrator로서는 자주 실패한다. Orchestrator의 근저에 있는 물리적 메커니즘을 밝히고 system uncertainty를 정량화함으로써, 우리의 발견은 향후 연구에서 Multi-Agent Systems의 architectural design development에 대한 통찰을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"63358","en":"Multi-Agent Teams Hold Experts Back","ko":"다중 에이전트 팀은 전문가를 저해한다","authors":"Aneesh Pappu, Batu El, Hancheng Cao, Carmelo di Nolfo, Yanchao Sun, Meng Cao, James Zou","pos":"#1909","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Xn8kmKvO9g","abs":"<p>Multi-agent LLM systems are increasingly deployed as autonomous collaborators, where agents interact freely rather than execute fixed, pre-specified workflows. In such settings, effective coordination cannot be fully designed in advance and must instead emerge through interaction. However, most prior work enforces coordination through fixed roles, workflows, or aggregation rules, leaving open the question of how well self-organizing teams perform when coordination is unconstrained. Drawing on organizational psychology, we study whether self-organizing LLM teams achieve <em>strong synergy</em>, where team performance matches or exceeds the best individual member. Across human-inspired and frontier ML benchmarks, we find that---unlike human teams---LLM teams consistently fail to match their expert agent's performance, even when explicitly told who the expert is, incurring performance losses of up to 37.6%. Decomposing this failure, we show that expert leveraging, rather than identification, is the primary bottleneck. Conversational analysis reveals a tendency toward integrative compromise---averaging expert and non-expert views rather than appropriately weighting expertise---which increases with team size and correlates negatively with performance. Interestingly, this consensus-seeking behavior improves robustness to adversarial agents, suggesting a trade-off between alignment and effective expertise utilization. Our findings reveal a significant gap in the ability of self-organizing multi-agent teams to harness the collective expertise of their members.</p>","absKo":"<p>Multi-agent LLM 시스템은 점점 더 자율적 협력자로 배치되고 있으며, 이들 agent는 고정된 사전 정의 workflow를 수행하기보다 자유롭게 상호작용한다. 이러한 설정에서는 효과적인 조정을 사전에 완전히 설계할 수 없고, 상호작용을 통해서만 emergent하게 나타나야 한다. 그러나 기존 연구의 대부분은 고정된 역할, workflow, 또는 aggregation rule을 통해 조정을 강제하며, 조정이 제약되지 않을 때 self-organizing team이 얼마나 잘 수행하는지에 대한 질문은 여전히 남아 있다. 조직심리학에 기반하여, 우리는 self-organizing LLM team이 <em>strong synergy</em>를 달성하는지, 즉 team 성능이 가장 뛰어난 개별 구성원의 성능과 같거나 그 이상인지 연구했다. 인간에서 영감을 받은 benchmark와 frontier ML benchmark 전반에서, 우리는 인간 team과 달리 LLM team이 expert agent의 성능에 일관되게 미치지 못함을 발견했다. 이는 누가 expert인지 명시적으로 알려주었을 때조차 마찬가지였으며, 최대 37.6%의 성능 손실을 초래했다. 이 실패를 분해해보면, identification보다 expert leveraging이 주요 병목임을 보인다. 대화 분석은 expert와 non-expert의 견해를 적절히 가중하기보다 평균내는 식의 integrative compromise 경향을 드러내며, 이는 team 규모가 커질수록 증가하고 성능과는 음의 상관을 보인다. 흥미롭게도, 이러한 consensus-seeking 행동은 adversarial agent에 대한 견고성을 향상시키며, 이는 alignment와 효과적인 expertise 활용 사이의 trade-off를 시사한다. 우리의 결과는 self-organizing multi-agent team이 구성원들의 집단적 전문성을 활용하는 능력에 상당한 격차가 있음을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"62913","en":"MonoScale: Scaling Multi-Agent System with Monotonic Improvement","ko":"MonoScale: 단조 증가를 통한 다중 에이전트 시스템 확장","authors":"Shuai Shao, Yixiang Liu, Bingwei Lu, Weinan Zhang","pos":"#1910","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=bwqwuJM68F","abs":"<p>In recent years, LLM-based multi-agent systems (MAS) have advanced rapidly, using a router to decompose tasks and delegate subtasks to specialized agents. A natural way to expand capability is to <strong>scale up the agent pool</strong> by continually integrating new functional agents or tool interfaces, but naive expansion can trigger <strong>performance collapse</strong> when the router cold-starts on newly added, heterogeneous, and unreliable agents. We propose <strong>MonoScale</strong>, an expansion-aware update framework that proactively generates a small set of agent-conditioned familiarization tasks, harvests evidence from both successful and failed interactions, and distills it into auditable natural-language memory to guide future routing. We formalize sequential augmentation as a contextual bandit and perform trust-region memory updates, yielding a monotonic non-decreasing performance guarantee across onboarding rounds. Experiments on GAIA and Humanity's Last Exam show stable gains as the agent pool grows, outperforming naive scale-up and strong-router fixed-pool baselines.</p>","absKo":"<p>최근 몇 년간 LLM 기반 multi-agent system(MAS)은 빠르게 발전해 왔으며, router를 사용해 task를 분해하고 하위 task를 전문 agent에 위임하고 있다. 기능적 agent나 tool interface를 지속적으로 통합해 <strong>agent pool을 확장하는 것</strong>은 capability를 자연스럽게 키우는 방법이지만, 새로 추가된 이질적이고 신뢰도가 낮은 agent들에 대해 router가 cold-start할 때 단순한 확장은 <strong>performance collapse</strong>를 유발할 수 있다. 우리는 <strong>MonoScale</strong>을 제안한다. 이는 expansion-aware update framework로, 소수의 agent-conditioned familiarization task를 선제적으로 생성하고, 성공 및 실패한 interaction 모두에서 evidence를 수집하며, 이를 감사 가능한 자연어 memory로 압축해 향후 routing을 돕는다. 우리는 sequential augmentation을 contextual bandit으로 정식화하고 trust-region memory update를 수행함으로써, onboarding round 전반에 걸쳐 성능이 단조 비감소하는 보장을 얻는다. GAIA와 Humanity's Last Exam 실험에서 agent pool이 커져도 안정적인 성능 향상을 보였으며, 단순한 scale-up과 강력한 router를 갖춘 fixed-pool baseline을 능가했다.</p>"},{"id":"60749","en":"MOC: Multi-Order Communication in LLM-based Multi-Agent Systems","ko":"MOC: LLM 기반 Multi-Agent System의 Multi-Order Communication","authors":"Yao Guan, Lin Wang, Zhihui Lu, Ziyi Wang, Wenzhu Yan, Qiang Duan","pos":"#1915","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=wyynWicO5s","abs":"<p>Despite the remarkable progress of Large Language Model (LLM) based Multi-Agent Systems, most research focuses on optimizing coordination topology while largely underexploring the equally critical problem: how to transmit and optimize messages among agents effectively? Current communication schemes typically rely on the direct concatenation of first-order neighbor responses, which induces a restricted evidence receptive field and leads to the dilution of crucial insights over multi-hop paths. To address these limitations, we propose the Multi-Order Communication (MOC) scheme, which reconstructs the inter-agent communication to capture multi-hop dependencies and incorporates a structural message consolidation strategy to ensure efficiency. Specifically, we formalize the communication mechanism to construct a structured multi-order evidence stream, and subsequently design a Semantic-Topological Merging algorithm to optimize semantic fidelity within token constraints. Extensive experiments across six diverse datasets and LLM backbones of varying parameter scales demonstrate that MOC consistently improves task performance and reduces communication costs.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large Language Model(LLM) 기반 Multi-Agent Systems의 괄목할 만한 진전에도 불구하고, 대부분의 연구는 coordination topology 최적화에 집중하는 반면, 동일하게 중요한 문제인 에이전트 간 메시지를 어떻게 효과적으로 전달하고 최적화할 것인가를 크게 간과해 왔다. 현재의 communication scheme은 일반적으로 1차 이웃 응답을 직접 이어 붙이는 방식에 의존하며, 이로 인해 제한된 evidence receptive field가 유발되고 multi-hop 경로를 따라 핵심 통찰이 희석된다. 이러한 한계를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 Multi-Order Communication(MOC) scheme을 제안한다. 이 scheme은 agent 간 communication을 재구성하여 multi-hop dependency를 포착하고, 효율성을 보장하기 위한 structural message consolidation strategy를 통합한다. 구체적으로, communication mechanism을 formalize하여 structured multi-order evidence stream을 구성하고, 이어서 token 제약 내에서 semantic fidelity를 최적화하는 Semantic-Topological Merging algorithm을 설계한다. 여섯 개의 다양한 dataset과 서로 다른 parameter scale의 LLM backbone 전반에 대한 광범위한 실험은 MOC가 일관되게 task performance를 향상시키고 communication cost를 줄임을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"65931","en":"Executable Agentic Memory for GUI Agent","ko":"GUI 에이전트를 위한 실행 가능한 에이전트 메모리","authors":"Zerui Qin, Sheng Yue, Xingyuan Hua, Yongjian Fu, Ju Ren","pos":"#2000","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=8metOwZHjD","abs":"Modern GUI agents typically rely on a model-centric and step-wise interaction paradigm, where LLMs must re-interpret the UI and re-decide actions at every screen, which is fragile in long-horizon tasks. In this paper, we propose Executable Agentic Memory (EAM), a structured Knowledge Graph (KG) that shifts GUI planning from free-form generation to a robust retrieval-and-execution process. Our approach includes a sample-efficient memory construction pipeline using state-aware DFS and action-group mining to compress multi-step routines. To ensure efficient planning, we introduce a value-guided graph search where a lightweight Q-function model steers Monte Carlo Tree Search (MCTS) over the KG. We theoretically establish bias-consistency for the Q-model and derive sample complexity bounds for path recovery. Empirically, EAM outperforms state-of-the-art baselines like UI-TARS-7B by up to $19.6\\%$ on AndroidWorld, while reducing token costs $6\\times$ relative to GPT-4o. With a $2.8$s average latency, EAM enables reliable, quick, and long-horizon GUI automation."},{"id":"61429","en":"Federated Sketching LoRA: A Flexible Framework for Heterogeneous Collaborative Fine-Tuning of LLMs","ko":"Federated Sketching LoRA: LLMs의 Heterogeneous Collaborative Fine-Tuning을 위한 유연한 Framework","authors":"Wenzhi Fang, Dong-Jun Han, Liangqi Yuan, Seyyedali Hosseinalipour, Christopher G. Brinton","pos":"#2002","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=qFKFSVvff5","abs":"<p>Fine-tuning large language models (LLMs) on resource-constrained clients remains a challenging problem. Recent works have fused low-rank adaptation (LoRA) techniques with federated fine-tuning to mitigate challenges associated with client model sizes and data scarcity. Still, the heterogeneity of resources remains a critical bottleneck: while higher-rank modules generally enhance performance, varying client capabilities constrain LoRA's feasible rank range. Existing approaches attempting to resolve this issue either lack analytical justification or impose additional computational overhead, leaving a wide gap for efficient and theoretically-grounded solutions. To address these challenges, we propose federated sketching LoRA (FSLoRA), which leverages a sketching mechanism to enable clients to selectively update submatrices of global LoRA modules maintained by the server. By adjusting the sketching ratios, which determine the ranks of the submatrices on the clients, FSLoRA flexibly adapts to client-specific communication and computational constraints. We provide a rigorous convergence analysis of FSLoRA that characterizes how the sketching ratios affect the convergence rate. Through extensive experiments, we demonstrate that FSLoRA outperforms baselines and significantly improves training efficiency while preserving stable convergence.</p>","absKo":"<p>자원 제약이 있는 클라이언트에서 대규모 언어 모델(LLM)을 fine-tuning하는 것은 여전히 어려운 문제이다. 최근 연구들은 client model size와 data scarcity와 관련된 어려움을 완화하기 위해 low-rank adaptation (LoRA) 기법을 federated fine-tuning과 결합해 왔다. 그럼에도 자원 이질성은 여전히 핵심 병목이다. 더 높은 rank의 module은 일반적으로 성능을 향상시키지만, 클라이언트별 상이한 역량은 LoRA가 사용할 수 있는 rank 범위를 제한한다. 이 문제를 해결하려는 기존 접근법은 분석적 타당성이 부족하거나 추가 계산 오버헤드를 유발하여, 효율적이면서 이론적으로 정당화된 해법과는 큰 간극이 남아 있다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해 우리는 federated sketching LoRA (FSLoRA)를 제안한다. FSLoRA는 sketching mechanism을 활용해 클라이언트가 서버가 유지하는 전역 LoRA module의 부분행렬(submatrix)만 선택적으로 업데이트하도록 한다. 클라이언트에서 부분행렬의 rank를 결정하는 sketching ratio를 조절함으로써, FSLoRA는 클라이언트별 통신 및 계산 제약에 유연하게 적응한다. 우리는 sketching ratio가 convergence rate에 미치는 영향을 특징짓는 FSLoRA의 엄밀한 convergence analysis를 제시한다. 광범위한 실험을 통해 FSLoRA가 baseline을 능가하고, 안정적인 수렴을 유지하면서도 학습 효율을 크게 향상시킴을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"63854","en":"Great Minds Think Alike: Contextual Tacit Communication for Decentralized LLM-Agent Cooperation","ko":"Great Minds Think Alike: 분산 LLM 에이전트 협력을 위한 문맥적 암묵적 통신","authors":"Yue Pei, Hongming Zhang, Jiarui Guan, Jusheng Zhang, Liang Lin, Haogang Zhu, Ziliang Chen","pos":"#2005","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=TA2eE0lJmf","abs":"<p>Large language models (LLMs) are increasingly used as planners for cooperative embodied agents, but multi-agent settings amplify inconsistency under partial observability and make explicit communication costly or even unavailable. Many existing approaches rely on online message passing; when communication is removed, agents often fall back to independent local planning that suffers from tacit miscoordination. We introduce Contextual Tacit Communication, a training-free protocol that aligns decentralized decisions with a joint LLM value score without explicit message actions. Our method measures context-conditioned value rectifications via residual banding to pinpoint miscoordination actions and amortizes the resulting coordination signals into a retrieval-augmented Tacit Rule Memory that provides prompt-level cooperation rules at execution time. Experiments on VIKI, C-WAH, and TDW-MAT show that our approach improves cooperation performance over baselines while reducing runtime overhead compared with communication-based methods.</p>","absKo":"<p>협력적 embodied agent를 위한 planner로서 large language models(LLMs)가 점점 더 많이 사용되고 있지만, multi-agent setting은 partial observability 하에서의 불일치를 증폭시키고 explicit communication을 비용이 크거나 아예 불가능한 것으로 만든다. 기존의 많은 접근은 online message passing에 의존하며, communication이 제거되면 agent들은 종종 암묵적 miscoordination을 겪는 independent local planning으로 돌아간다. 우리는 explicit message actions 없이 decentralized decisions를 joint LLM value score에 정렬하는 training-free protocol인 Contextual Tacit Communication을 제안한다. 본 방법은 residual banding을 통해 context-conditioned value rectification을 측정하여 miscoordination actions를 pinpoint하고, 그 결과로 얻어진 coordination signals를 retrieval-augmented Tacit Rule Memory에 amortize하여 execution time에 prompt-level cooperation rules를 제공한다. VIKI, C-WAH, TDW-MAT에서의 실험은 본 접근이 communication-based method에 비해 runtime overhead를 줄이면서도 baseline보다 cooperation performance를 향상시킴을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"61572","en":"LRAgent: Efficient KV Cache Sharing for Multi-LoRA LLM Agents","ko":"LRAgent: Multi-LoRA LLM Agents를 위한 효율적인 KV Cache Sharing","authors":"Hyesung Jeon, Hyeongju Ha, jae-joon kim","pos":"#2011","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ooRukY3zjQ","abs":"Role specialization in multi-LLM agent systems is often realized via multi-LoRA, where agents share a pretrained backbone and differ only through lightweight adapters. Despite sharing base model weights, each agent independently builds and stores its own KV cache for the same long, tool-augmented trajectories, incurring substantial memory and compute overhead. Existing KV cache sharing methods largely overlook this multi-LoRA setting. We observe that, across agents, cache differences are dominated by adapter outputs, while activations from the shared pretrained backbone remain highly similar. Based on this observation, we propose LRAgent, a KV cache sharing framework for multi-LoRA agents that decomposes the cache into a shared base component from the pretrained weights and an adapter-dependent component from LoRA weights. LRAgent reduces memory overhead by sharing the base component and storing the adapter component in its inherent low-rank form, and further reduces compute overhead, enabled by shared-$A$ multi-LoRA architectures, by also sharing the low-rank cache and avoiding redundant computations for contexts already processed by other agents. To efficiently reconstruct adapter contributions at runtime, we introduce Flash-LoRA-Attention, a kernel that reorders attention computation to avoid materializing the low-rank cache to full dimension. LRAgent achieves throughput and time-to-first-token latency close to fully shared caching, while preserving accuracy near the non-shared caching baseline across agentic question-answering benchmarks.","absKo":"multi-LLM agent system에서 role specialization은 종종 multi-LoRA를 통해 구현되며, 이때 agent는 pretrained backbone을 공유하고 lightweight adapter만 다르다. base model weight를 공유함에도 불구하고, 각 agent는 동일한 긴 tool-augmented trajectory에 대해 자신만의 KV cache를 독립적으로 구성하고 저장하므로 상당한 memory 및 compute overhead가 발생한다. 기존 KV cache sharing 방법은 이 multi-LoRA 설정을 대체로 간과한다. 우리는 agent들 사이에서 cache 차이가 주로 adapter output에 의해 지배되는 반면, 공유된 pretrained backbone의 activation은 매우 유사하다는 사실을 관찰한다. 이러한 관찰에 기반하여, 우리는 cache를 pretrained weight에서 비롯된 shared base component와 LoRA weight에서 비롯된 adapter-dependent component로 분해하는 multi-LoRA agent용 KV cache sharing framework인 LRAgent를 제안한다. LRAgent는 base component를 공유하고 adapter component를 고유한 low-rank 형태로 저장함으로써 memory overhead를 줄이며, shared-$A$ multi-LoRA architecture를 통해 가능해진 shared low-rank cache와 다른 agent가 이미 처리한 context에 대한 중복 계산 회피를 통해 compute overhead도 추가로 줄인다. 런타임에 adapter 기여를 효율적으로 복원하기 위해, 우리는 low-rank cache를 full dimension으로 materialize하지 않도록 attention computation을 재배열하는 kernel인 Flash-LoRA-Attention을 도입한다. LRAgent는 fully shared caching에 가까운 throughput과 time-to-first-token latency를 달성하면서도, agentic question-answering benchmark 전반에서 non-shared caching baseline에 근접한 정확도를 유지한다."},{"id":"66695","en":"LiftQuant: Continuous Bit-Width Control for Pareto-Optimal LLM Deployment","ko":"LiftQuant: Pareto 최적 LLM 배포를 위한 연속 Bit-Width 제어","authors":"Liulu He, Xuan Ang Liu, Juntao Liu, Taolue Feng, Ting Lu, Chunsheng Gan, ZHIYV PENG, Yuan Du, Li Du, Huanrui Yang, Yijiang Liu","pos":"#2014","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=1GvXUhLIMP","abs":"<p>Existing quantization methods are fundamentally limited by rigid, integer-based bit-widths (e.g., 2, 3-bit), creating a \"deployment gap\" where LLMs cannot be optimally fitted to specific memory budgets. To bridge this gap, we introduce LiftQuant, a novel framework that enables continuous bit-width control for true Pareto-optimal deployment. The core innovation is a \"lift-then-project\" mechanism: we represent d-dimensional weight vectors by projecting a simple 1-bit lattice from a tunable D-dimensional \"lifted\" space. By adjusting the lifted dimension D, LiftQuant naturally yields an effective bit-width of D/d, allowing for seamless, continuous resolution adjustment rather than discrete steps. This projection generates a structured yet non-uniform codebook, capturing the expressive power of Vector Quantization. Crucially, its decoding path relies solely on linear transformations and 1-bit uniform quantizers, retaining hardware-friendly efficiency. This flexibility is transformative: LiftQuant enables a 70B LLM to be compressed to 2.4 bits to precisely fit a 24GB GPU, where its performance significantly surpasses state-of-the-art 2-bit models. With a decoding throughput up to 6.7x faster than FP16, LiftQuant redefines compression as a continuous optimization problem, paving the way for a new generation of hardware-aware LLM deployment.</p>"},{"id":"63290","en":"MAS-Architect: Declarative Multi-Agent System Design via Separation of Concerns","ko":"MAS-Architect: 관심사 분리를 통한 선언적 다중 에이전트 시스템 설계","authors":"Jing Huang, Lidong Zhang, Mutian Bao, Yadong Li, Xingzhong Xu, Jinjian Zhang, Jie Liu, Ming Kong, Qiang Zhu","pos":"#2016","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=YLP0nvtUNw","abs":"<p>The Automated Design of Multi-Agent Systems (Auto-MAS) has emerged as a promising framework for addressing complex reasoning tasks. However, existing approaches often suffer from structural rigidity  and entangle the design of system topology with the implementation of individual agents. To overcome these limitations, we propose MAS-Architect, a framework that automates MAS design through a novel code-based declarative MAS paradigm rooted in the \\textit{Separation of Concerns} principle. By decoupling topology planning from node implementation via a unified interface, our approach enables the from-scratch generation of task-adaptive architectures. We further employ a \\textit{Distill-then-Explore} training strategy to optimize these designs. Comprehensive experiments on five benchmarks show that MAS-Architect sets a new Pareto frontier in the efficiency–performance trade-off: it surpasses state-of-the-art methods while substantially lowering token usage. Notably, the framework achieves a strong average accuracy of 78.7\\% across benchmarks with an inference cost of only 2,533 tokens per query. Qualitative analysis reveals the autonomous emergence of advanced collaboration patterns, validating the generative flexibility of the declarative paradigm. Code and data will be released.</p>","absKo":"<p>Automated Design of Multi-Agent Systems (Auto-MAS)는 복잡한 추론 작업을 다루기 위한 유망한 framework로 부상했다. 그러나 기존 접근법은 구조적 경직성으로 인해 자주 어려움을 겪고, system topology 설계와 개별 agent 구현을 서로 얽어 놓는다. 이러한 한계를 극복하기 위해 우리는 \\textit{Separation of Concerns} 원칙에 뿌리를 둔 새로운 code-based declarative MAS paradigm을 통해 MAS 설계를 자동화하는 framework인 MAS-Architect를 제안한다. 통합된 interface를 통해 topology planning과 node implementation을 분리함으로써, 우리의 접근법은 task-adaptive architecture를 처음부터 생성할 수 있게 한다. 또한 이러한 설계를 최적화하기 위해 \\textit{Distill-then-Explore} training strategy를 사용한다. 다섯 개 benchmark에 대한 포괄적 실험은 MAS-Architect가 efficiency-performance trade-off에서 새로운 Pareto frontier를 설정함을 보여준다. 즉, state-of-the-art method를 능가하면서 token 사용량은 크게 줄인다. 특히 이 framework는 query당 inference cost가 단 2,533 tokens임에도 benchmark 전반에서 평균 78.7\\%의 강력한 accuracy를 달성한다. 정성적 분석은 고급 협업 패턴의 자율적 출현을 보여주며, declarative paradigm의 생성적 유연성을 검증한다. Code와 data는 공개될 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"62216","en":"Evolutionary Generation of Multi-Agent Systems","ko":"Multi-Agent Systems의 진화적 생성","authors":"Yuntong Hu, Matthew Trager, Yuting Zhang, Yi Zhang, Shuo Yang, Wei Xia, Stefano Soatto","pos":"#2100","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ic0AGRIkmY","abs":"<p>Large language model (LLM)–based multi-agent systems (MAS) show strong promise for complex reasoning, planning, and tool-augmented tasks, but designing effective MAS architectures remains labor-intensive, brittle, and hard to generalize. Existing automatic MAS generation methods either rely on code generation, which often leads to executability and robustness failures, or impose rigid architectural templates that limit expressiveness and adaptability. We propose Evolutionary Generation of Multi-Agent Systems (EvoMAS), which formulates MAS generation as structured configuration generation. EvoMAS performs evolutionary generation in configuration space. Specifically, EvoMAS selects initial configurations from a pool, applies feedbackconditioned mutation and crossover guided by execution traces, and iteratively refines both the candidate pool and an experience memory. We evaluate EvoMAS on diverse benchmarks, including BBEH, SWE-Bench, and WorkBench, covering reasoning, software engineering, and tool-use tasks. EvoMAS consistently improves task performance over both human-designed MAS and prior automatic MAS generation methods, while producing generated systems with higher executability and runtime robustness. EvoMAS outperforms the agent evolution method EvoAgent by +10.5 points on BBEH reasoning and +7.1 points on WorkBench. With Claude-4.5-Sonnet, EvoMAS also reaches 79.1% on SWE-BenchVerified, matching the top of the leaderboard.</p>"},{"id":"66001","en":"Decentralized Instruction Tuning: Conflict-Aware Splitting and Weight Merging","ko":"탈중앙화 지시 튜닝: 충돌 인식 분할과 가중치 병합","authors":"Minsik Choi, Geewook Kim","pos":"#2107","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=827XA57r8F","abs":"<p>Instruction tuning aligns large (multimodal) language models with diverse user intents, but scaling to heterogeneous mixtures is hindered by (i) gradient interference that causes negative transfer and stiff high-curvature dynamics, and (ii) bandwidth-heavy synchronization that is often impractical on fragmented compute. We propose MERIT, a decentralized, merge-ready pipeline that splits mixtures before fine-tuning. Starting from a merge-ready initialization, MERIT estimates dataset-level gradients, builds a cosine-similarity conflict matrix, applies PCA to extract dominant conflict axes, and partitions datasets accordingly. Each partition is fine-tuned independently with no inter-partition communication, and merged once via one-shot token-weighted averaging. A local quadratic flat-basin analysis shows that merging acts as a curvature-weighted spectral filter, and that PCA-aligned splitting amplifies cancellation of high-curvature disagreement components. On Qwen2.5-VL-3B fine-tuned on 136 Vision-FLAN tasks, MERIT improves the overall benchmark average from 54.7 (centralized joint training) to 57.0 while enabling communication-free parallel fine-tuning. We further validate MERIT at 7B scale on a 1.6M-example mixture and on text-only instruction mixtures.</p>"},{"id":"66421","en":"ComplexMCP: Evaluation of LLM Agents in Dynamic, Interdependent, and Large-Scale Tool Sandbox","ko":"ComplexMCP: 동적이고 상호 의존적이며 대규모인 도구 샌드박스에서 LLM 에이전트 평가","authors":"Yuanyang Li, Xue Yang, Longyue Wang, Weihua Luo, Hongyang Chen","pos":"#2116","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=3u1M9wokD7","abs":"Current LLM agents are proficient at calling isolated APIs but struggle with the \"last mile\" of commercial software automation. In real-world scenarios, tools are not independent; they are atomic, interdependent, and prone to environmental noise. We introduce $\\textbf{ComplexMCP}$, a benchmark designed to evaluate agents in these rigorous conditions. Built on the Model Context Protocol (MCP), $\\textbf{ComplexMCP}$ provides over 300 meticulously tested tools derived from 7 stateful sandboxes, ranging from office suites to financial systems. Unlike existing datasets, our benchmark utilizes a seed-driven architecture to simulate dynamic environment states and unpredictable API failures, ensuring a deterministic yet diverse evaluation.  We evaluate various LLMs across full-context and RAG paradigms, revealing a stark performance gap: even top-tier models fail to exceed a 60% success rate, far trailing human performance 90%. Granular trajectory analysis identifies three fundamental bottlenecks: (1) $\\textbf{tool retrieval saturation}$ as action spaces scale; (2) $\\textbf{over-confidence}$, where agents skip essential environment verifications; and (3) $\\textbf{strategic defeatism}$, a tendency to rationalize failure rather than pursuing recovery. These findings underscore the insufficiency of current agents for interdependent workflows, positioning $\\textbf{ComplexMCP}$ as a critical testbed for the next generation of resilient autonomous systems."},{"id":"64488","en":"Agent Learning via Early Experience","ko":"초기 경험을 통한 에이전트 학습","authors":"Kai Zhang, Xiangchao Chen, Bo Liu, Tianci Xue, Zeyi Liao, Zhihan Liu, xiyao wang, Yuting Ning, Zhaorun Chen, Xiaohan Fu, Jian Xie, Yuxuan Sun, Boyu Gou, Qi Qi, Zihang Meng, Jianwei Yang, Ning Zhang, Xian Li, Ashish Shah, Dat Huynh, Hengduo Li, Zi Yang, Xuefei Cao, Lawrence Jang, Shuyan Zhou, Jiacheng Zhu, Huan Sun, JASON WESTON, Yu Su, Yifan Wu","pos":"#2201","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=N3dXUHY5dD","abs":"<p>A long-term goal of language agents is to learn and improve through their own experience, ultimately outperforming humans in complex, real-world tasks. However, training agents from experience data with reinforcement learning remains difficult in many environments, which either lack verifiable rewards (e.g., websites) or require inefficient long-horizon rollouts (e.g., multi-turn tool use). As a result, most current agents rely on supervised fine-tuning on expert data, which is challenging to scale and generalizes poorly. This limitation stems from the nature of expert demonstrations: they capture only a narrow range of scenarios, and expose the agent to limited environment diversity. We address this limitation with a middle-ground paradigm we call <em>early experience</em>: interaction data generated by the agent's own actions, where the resulting future states serve as supervision without reward signals. Within this paradigm, we study two strategies of using such data: (1) implicit world modeling, which uses collected states to ground the policy in environment dynamics; and (2) self-reflection, where the agent learns from its suboptimal actions to improve reasoning and decision-making. Evaluation across eight diverse environments and multiple model families shows that our approaches consistently improve effectiveness and out-of-domain generalization, highlighting the value of early experience. Moreover, in environments with verifiable rewards, our results provide promising signals that early experience offers a strong foundation for subsequent reinforcement learning, making it a practical bridge between imitation learning and fully experience-driven agents.</p>","absKo":"<p>language agent가 장기적으로 스스로의 경험을 통해 학습하고 개선하여, 궁극적으로 복잡한 실제 작업에서 인간을 능가하는 것은 중요한 목표이다. 그러나 reinforcement learning으로 경험 데이터에서 agent를 학습시키는 일은 많은 환경에서 여전히 어렵다. 이는 검증 가능한 reward가 없거나(예: website), 비효율적인 장기 rollout이 필요한 경우(예: multi-turn tool use) 때문이기도 하다. 그 결과, 현재의 대부분 agent는 expert data에 대한 supervised fine-tuning에 의존하는데, 이는 확장하기 어렵고 일반화도 잘되지 않는다. 이러한 한계는 expert demonstration의 특성에서 비롯된다. 즉, demonstration은 좁은 범위의 scenario만 포착하며 agent를 제한된 environment diversity에만 노출시킨다. 우리는 이 한계를 <em>early experience</em>라고 부르는 중간 지대 paradigm으로 해결한다. 이는 agent 자신의 action이 생성한 interaction data로, 그 결과로 생긴 미래 state가 reward signal 없이 supervision 역할을 한다. 이 paradigm 내에서 우리는 이러한 data를 사용하는 두 가지 전략을 연구한다. (1) implicit world modeling은 수집된 state를 사용해 policy를 environment dynamics에 접지시키고, (2) self-reflection은 agent가 자신의 suboptimal action에서 학습하여 reasoning과 decision-making을 개선한다. 여덟 개의 다양한 environment와 여러 model family에 대한 평가는 우리의 접근법이 일관되게 effectiveness와 out-of-domain generalization을 향상시킴을 보여주며, early experience의 가치를 강조한다. 더욱이, 검증 가능한 reward가 있는 environment에서 우리의 결과는 early experience가 후속 reinforcement learning을 위한 강력한 기반을 제공함을 시사하는 유망한 신호를 제공하며, imitation learning과 완전한 experience-driven agent 사이의 실용적 가교가 될 수 있음을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"65356","en":"AgentXRay: White-Boxing Agentic Systems via Workflow Reconstruction","ko":"AgentXRay: 워크플로 재구성을 통한 에이전트 시스템 화이트박싱","authors":"Ruijie Shi, Houbin Zhang, Yuecheng Han, Yuheng Wang, Jingru Fan, Runde Yang, Yufan Dang, Huatao Li, Dewen Liu, Yuan Cheng, Chen Qian","pos":"#2203","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=EPL2YoeGow","abs":"<p>Large Language Models have shown strong capabilities in complex problem solving, yet many agentic systems remain difficult to interpret and control due to opaque internal workflows. While some frameworks offer explicit architectures for collaboration, many deployed agentic systems operate as black boxes to users. We address this by introducing Agentic Workflow Reconstruction (AWR), a new task aiming to synthesize an explicit, interpretable stand-in workflow that approximates a black-box system using only input--output access. We propose AgentXRay, a search-based framework that formulates AWR as a combinatorial optimization problem over discrete agent roles and tool invocations in a chain-structured workflow space. Unlike model distillation, AgentXRay produces editable white-box workflows that match target outputs under an observable, output-based proxy metric, without accessing model parameters. To navigate the vast search space, AgentXRay employs Monte Carlo Tree Search enhanced by a scoring-based Red-Black Pruning mechanism, which dynamically integrates proxy quality with search depth. Experiments across diverse domains demonstrate that AgentXRay achieves higher proxy similarity and reduces token consumption compared to unpruned search, enabling deeper workflow exploration under fixed iteration budgets.</p>"},{"id":"63163","en":"CORRECT: COndensed eRror RECognition via knowledge Transfer in multi-agent systems","ko":"CORRECT: 다중 에이전트 시스템에서 지식 전이를 통한 압축 오류 인식","authors":"Yifan Yu, Moyan Li, Shaoyuan Xu, Jinmiao Fu, Xinhai Hou, Fan Lai, Bryan Wang","pos":"#2210","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ZUDdYZSwr4","abs":"<p>Multi-agent systems (MAS) are increasingly capable of tackling complex real-world tasks, yet their reliance on inter-agent coordination, tool use, and long-horizon reasoning makes error recognition particularly challenging. Minor errors can propagate across agents, escalating into task failures while producing long, intertwined execution trajectories that impose significant costs for both human developers and automated systems to debug and analyze. Our key insight is that, despite surface differences in failure trajectories (e.g., logs), MAS errors often recur with similar structural patterns. This paper presents CORRECT, the first lightweight, training-free framework that leverages an online cache of distilled error schemata to recognize and transfer knowledge of failure structures across new requests. This cache-based reuse allows LLMs to perform targeted error localization at inference time, avoiding the need for expensive retraining while adapting to dynamic MAS deployments in subseconds. To support rigorous study in this domain, we also introduce CORRECT-Error, a large-scale dataset of over 2,000 annotated trajectories collected through a novel error-injection pipeline guided by real-world distributions, and further validated through human evaluation to ensure alignment with natural failure patterns. Experiments across seven diverse MAS applications show that CORRECT improves step-level error localization up to 19.8% over existing advances while at near-zero overhead, substantially narrowing the gap between automated and human-level error recognition.</p>","absKo":"<p>Multi-agent system(MAS)은 점점 더 복잡한 실제 task를 다룰 수 있게 되었지만, agent 간 coordination, tool 사용, long-horizon 추론에 의존하기 때문에 error recognition이 특히 어렵다. 작은 오류도 agent 전반으로 전파되어 task failure로 확대될 수 있으며, 길고 서로 얽힌 execution trajectory를 만들어 인간 개발자와 자동화 시스템 모두에게 디버깅과 분석에 큰 비용을 초래한다. 우리의 핵심 통찰은 표면적으로 다른 failure trajectory(예: log)가 존재하더라도, MAS 오류는 종종 유사한 structural pattern으로 재발한다는 점이다. 본 논문은 새로운 요청 전반에 걸쳐 failure structure에 대한 지식을 인식하고 전달하기 위해 distilled error schema의 online cache를 활용하는, 최초의 경량 training-free framework인 CORRECT를 제시한다. 이러한 cache 기반 재사용은 LLM이 inference time에 targeted error localization을 수행할 수 있게 하여, 동적 MAS 배포 환경에 서브초 단위로 적응하면서도 비용이 큰 재학습을 피하게 한다. 이 분야의 엄밀한 연구를 지원하기 위해, 우리는 또한 실제 분포에 의해 유도된 새로운 error-injection pipeline을 통해 수집된 2,000개 이상의 주석된 trajectory로 구성된 대규모 데이터셋 CORRECT-Error를 도입한다. 이 데이터셋은 자연스러운 failure pattern과의 정렬을 보장하기 위해 human evaluation으로 추가 검증되었다. 7개의 다양한 MAS application에서의 실험은 CORRECT가 기존 발전 대비 step-level error localization을 최대 19.8% 향상시키며, 오버헤드는 거의 0에 가깝게 유지하여 자동화된 error recognition과 인간 수준의 error recognition 간 격차를 크게 좁힘을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"65619","en":"When Agents Go Rogue: Activation-Based Detection of Malicious Behaviors in Multi-Agent Systems","ko":"에이전트가 폭주할 때: 멀티에이전트 시스템에서 활성화 기반 악성 행위 탐지","authors":"Haowen Xu, Xue Tan, Lei Ma, Zhihao Zhang, CHAO WANG, Qingze Wang, Ping Chen, Jun Dai, Xiaoyan Sun","pos":"#3100","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=BnduUW8izq","abs":"<p>While enabling effective collaboration on complex tasks, LLM-based Multi-Agent Systems (MAS) face critical security challenges due to vulnerabilities at the agent and interaction levels. Most existing MAS security defenses are built upon two core assumptions: semantically-explicit malicious attacks and explicit graph-based modeling of the MAS topology and agent-level interactions. In practice, real-world attacks are becoming more semantically stealthy, while MAS execution is typically asynchronous without the temporal alignment assumed by graph-based propagation models. To address these limitations, we propose AcMAS, an activation-based framework for malicious-behavior detection in MAS. By analyzing internal reasoning states in the activation space of local agents, AcMAS detects even stealthy attacks in a synchronization-robust fashion, without relying on explicit interaction graphs. Moreover, our activation analysis provides critical signals to guide AcMAS in restoring the functionality of compromised agents, rather than the disruptive agent isolation commonly used by the state-of-the-art methods. Comprehensive evaluation demonstrates that AcMAS significantly outperforms graph-based baselines against stealthy attacks, by +0.22 F1 in synchronous settings (0.94 vs. 0.72) and by +0.55 F1 in asynchronous settings (0.93 vs. 0.38), with generalization across diverse open-source LLM backbones, attack intensity, and MAS scale.</p>"},{"id":"66298","en":"Adaptive Code Watermarking Through Reinforcement Learning","ko":"강화 학습을 통한 적응형 코드 워터마킹","authors":"Zhimeng Guo, Huaisheng Zhu, Siyuan Xu, Hangfan Zhang, Teng Xiao, Minhao Cheng","pos":"#4001","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=4xjq3iR4aK","abs":"<p>As LLMs increasingly generate production code, protecting intellectual property demands watermarking techniques that respect code's strict syntactic constraints. In this work, we introduce CodeTracer, an innovative adaptive code watermarking framework underpinned by a reinforcement learning training paradigm. At its core, CodeTracer features a policy-driven approach that utilizes a parameterized model to intelligently bias token choices during next-token prediction. This strategy ensures that embedded watermarks maintain code functionality while exhibiting subtle yet statistically detectable deviations from typical token distributions. To facilitate policy learning, we devise a comprehensive reward system that seamlessly integrates execution feedback with watermark embedding signals, balancing process-level and outcome-level rewards. To enable gradient-based optimization of these discrete watermarking decisions, we employ Gumbel Top-k reparameterization. Extensive comparative evaluations demonstrate that CodeTracer outperforms state-of-the-art baselines across multiple benchmarks in both watermark detectability and code functionality. Our code is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/CodeTracer-B8EE.</p>"},{"id":"65500","en":"Lifting Traces to Logic: Programmatic Skill Induction with Neuro-Symbolic Learning for Long-Horizon Agentic Tasks","ko":"트레이스를 논리로 승격: 장기 지평선 에이전트 과제를 위한 Neuro-Symbolic 학습 기반 프로그램적 스킬 유도","authors":"Jie-Jing Shao, Haiyan Yin, Yueming LYU, Xingrui Yu, Lan-Zhe Guo, Ivor Tsang, James Kwok, Yu-Feng Li","pos":"#4007","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=D0Dg8ISjq0","abs":"<p>Foundation model-driven agents often struggle with long-horizon planning due to the transient nature of purely prompting-based reasoning. While existing skill induction methods mitigate this by distilling experience into state-blind parameterized scripts, they fail to capture the conditional logic required for robust execution in dynamic environments. In this paper, we propose Neuro-Symbolic Skill Induction (NSI), a framework that lifts interaction traces into modular, \\textit{logic-grounded} programs. By synthesizing explicit control flows and dynamic variable binding, NSI empowers agents to discover \\textit{when} and \\textit{why} to act. This paradigm enables the efficient generalization, allowing agents to induce skills from few-shot examples and flexibly adapt to unseen goals. Experiments on a series of agentic tasks demonstrate that NSI consistently outperforms state-of-the-art baselines, empowering agents to self-evolve into architects of cognitive skills.</p>"},{"id":"62040","en":"ThunderAgent: A Fast, Simple, and Program-Aware Agentic Inference System","ko":"ThunderAgent: 빠르고 단순한 Program-Aware Agentic Inference 시스템","authors":"Hao Kang, Ziyang Li, Xinyu Yang, Weili Xu, Yinfang Chen, Junxiong Wang, Beidi Chen, Tushar Krishna, Chenfeng Xu, Simran Arora","pos":"#4304","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=kR4iOTaAOJ","abs":"<p>Large language models (LLMs) are now used to power complex multi-turn agentic workflows. Existing services run agentic inference by assembling isolated components: an LLM inference engine (e.g., vLLM) and a tool orchestrator (e.g., Kubernetes). Although agentic workflows involve multiple LLM and tool requests, existing services make scheduling decisions on a per-request basis, without end-to-end knowledge of the workflow. This leads to sub-optimal management of KV-caches and tool execution environments.  To address the challenges, we propose \\ouralg, an inference system that is aware of the end-to-end agent workflow. We abstract agentic workflows as \\textit{LLM Programs}, enabling a unified view of heterogeneous resources, including KV caches, system states, and external tool assets such as disk memory and network ports. \\ouralg introduces a program-aware scheduler and a tool resource manager designed to maximize KV cache hit rates, mitigate memory imbalances, and enable asynchronous environment preparation. Evaluations across coding, routing, and scientific discovery agents demonstrate that \\ouralg achieves <strong>1.5-3.6x</strong> throughput improvements in serving, <strong>1.8-3.9x</strong> in RL rollout, and up to <strong>4.2x</strong> disk memory savings compared to state-of-the-art inference systems.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large language model (LLM)은 이제 복잡한 multi-turn agentic workflow를 구동하는 데 사용된다. 기존 서비스는 LLM inference engine(예: vLLM)과 tool orchestrator(예: Kubernetes)를 분리된 구성요소로 조합하여 agentic inference를 실행한다. agentic workflow는 여러 LLM 및 tool request를 포함하지만, 기존 서비스는 workflow 전체에 대한 end-to-end knowledge 없이 request 단위로 scheduling 결정을 내린다. 그 결과 KV-cache와 tool execution environment를 최적으로 관리하지 못한다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해 우리는 end-to-end agent workflow를 인지하는 inference system인 \\ouralg를 제안한다. 우리는 agentic workflow를 \\textit{LLM Programs}로 추상화하여, KV cache, system state, disk memory와 network port 같은 external tool asset을 포함한 이질적 자원들을 통합적으로 볼 수 있게 한다. \\ouralg는 KV cache hit rate를 극대화하고, memory imbalance를 완화하며, 비동기 environment 준비를 가능하게 하는 program-aware scheduler와 tool resource manager를 도입한다. coding, routing, scientific discovery agent 전반의 평가에서 \\ouralg는 state-of-the-art inference system 대비 serving에서는 <strong>1.5-3.6x</strong>, RL rollout에서는 <strong>1.8-3.9x</strong>의 throughput 향상과 최대 <strong>4.2x</strong>의 disk memory 절감을 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"63308","en":"Outrunning LLM Cutoffs: A Live Kernel Crash Resolution Benchmark for All","ko":"LLM 지식 컷오프 앞지르기: 모두를 위한 실시간 커널 크래시 해결 벤치마크","authors":"Chenxi Huang, Alex Mathai, Feiyang Yu, Aleksandr Nogikh, Petros Maniatis, Franjo Ivancic, Eugene Wu, Kostis Kaffes, Junfeng Yang, Baishakhi Ray","pos":"#4308","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=YFY4rGLJmW","abs":"<p>Repairing system crashes discovered by kernel fuzzers like Syzkaller is a critical yet underexplored challenge in software engineering. While recent works have introduced Large Language Model (LLM) based agents for Linux kernel crash-resolution, their evaluation benchmarks are usually static and thus, do not capture the evolving nature of the Linux kernel, and suffer from potential data contamination due to LLM knowledge cutoffs. To address the above problem, we present (i) Live-kBench, an evaluation framework for self-evolving benchmarks that continuously scrapes and evaluates agents on freshly discovered kernel bugs, and (ii) kEnv, an agent-agnostic standardized crash-resolution environment for kernel compilation, execution, and feedback. This design decouples agent workflows from heavy-weight execution, enabling fair and scalable comparison across diverse agent frameworks under identical conditions.  To this end, we curate an inaugural dataset of 534 Linux kernel bugs and empirically demonstrate a significant performance gap, with agents achieving up to 25% higher equivalent patch rate on bugs fixed before the LLM knowledge cutoff. Using kEnv, we benchmark three state-of-the-art agents, showing that they resolve 74% of crashes on the first attempt (plausible patches); however only ~20% of generated patches closely match developer fixes. Additionally, exposing crash resolution feedback improves crash resolution rate by 29%. Live-kBench provides the community with an evaluation infrastructure for self-evolving benchmarks that is both time and attribute sensitive; complete with a public dashboard to track agent progress on Linux kernel bugs.</p>","absKo":"<p>Syzkaller 같은 kernel fuzzer가 발견한 system crash를 수리하는 일은 critical하지만 아직 충분히 탐구되지 않은 software engineering challenge입니다. 최근 연구들은 Linux kernel crash-resolution을 위한 Large Language Model (LLM) 기반 agent를 제시했지만, 이들의 evaluation benchmark는 대체로 정적이어서 Linux kernel의 진화하는 특성을 포착하지 못하며, LLM knowledge cutoff로 인한 잠재적 data contamination 문제도 안고 있습니다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해 우리는 (i) Live-kBench, 즉 새로 발견된 kernel bug를 지속적으로 수집하고 agent를 평가하는 self-evolving benchmark용 evaluation framework와, (ii) kEnv, 즉 kernel compilation, execution, feedback을 위한 agent-agnostic standardized crash-resolution environment를 제시합니다. 이 설계는 agent workflow를 무거운 execution으로부터 분리하여, 동일한 조건에서 다양한 agent framework를 공정하고 확장 가능하게 비교할 수 있게 합니다. 이를 위해 우리는 534개의 Linux kernel bug로 구성된 최초 데이터셋을 구축하고, LLM knowledge cutoff 이전에 수정된 bug에서는 agent가 최대 25% 더 높은 equivalent patch rate를 달성한다는 점을 실증적으로 보여줍니다. kEnv를 사용해 최신 three state-of-the-art agent를 벤치마크한 결과, 이들은 첫 시도에서 crash의 74%를 해결했지만(plausible patch), 생성된 patch 중 개발자 수정과 밀접하게 일치하는 것은 약 20%에 불과했습니다. 또한 crash resolution feedback을 노출하면 crash resolution rate가 29% 향상됩니다. Live-kBench는 시계열 및 속성에 민감한 self-evolving benchmark를 위한 evaluation infrastructure를 커뮤니티에 제공하며, Linux kernel bug에서의 agent 진척 상황을 추적할 수 있는 공개 dashboard도 포함합니다.</p>"},{"id":"66460","en":"TopBench: A Benchmark for Implicit Prediction and Reasoning over Tabular Question Answering","ko":"TopBench: 표 형식 질의응답에 대한 암묵적 예측 및 추론 벤치마크","authors":"An-Yang Ji, Jun-Peng Jiang, De-Chuan Zhan, Han-Jia Ye","pos":"#1700","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=3V1dG9Jp8E","abs":"<p>Large Language Models (LLMs) have advanced Table Question Answering, where most queries can be answered by extracting information or simple aggregation. However, a common class of real-world queries is implicitly predictive, requiring the inference of unobserved answers from historical patterns rather than mere retrieval. These queries introduce two challenges: recognizing latent intent and reliable predictive reasoning over massive tables. To assess LLMs in such Tabular questiOn answering with implicit Prediction tasks, we introduce TopBench, a benchmark consisting of 779 samples across four sub-tasks, ranging from single-point prediction to decision making, treatment effect analysis, and complex filtering, requiring models to generate outputs spanning reasoning text and structured tables. We evaluate diverse models under both text-based and agentic workflows. Experiments reveal that current models often struggle with intent recognition, defaulting to just lookups. Deeper analysis identifies that accurate intent disambiguation serves as the prerequisite for leading these predictive behaviors.  Furthermore, elevating the upper bound of prediction precision requires the integration of more sophisticated modeling or reasoning capabilities.</p>"},{"id":"64422","en":"Hunt Instead of Wait: Evaluating Deep Data Research on Large Language Models","ko":"기다리지 말고 사냥하라: 대형 언어 모델에서 심층 데이터 연구 평가","authors":"Wei Liu, Peijie Yu, Michele Orini, Yali Du, Yulan He","pos":"#2007","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=NooBkSo7oz","abs":"<p>The agency expected of Agentic Large Language Models goes beyond answering correctly, requiring autonomy to set goals and decide what to explore. We term this <em>investigatory intelligence</em>, distinguishing it from <em>executional intelligence</em>, which merely completes assigned tasks. Data Science provides a natural testbed, as real-world analysis starts from raw data rather than explicit queries, yet few benchmarks focus on it. To address this, we introduce <strong>Deep Data Research (DDR)</strong>, an open-ended task where LLMs autonomously extract key insights from databases, and <strong>DDR-Bench</strong>, a large-scale, checklist-based benchmark that enables verifiable evaluation. Results show that while frontier models display emerging agency, long-horizon exploration remains challenging. Our analysis highlights that effective investigatory intelligence depends not only on agent scaffolding or merely scaling, but also on intrinsic strategies of agentic models.</p>","absKo":"Agentic Large Language Model에 기대되는 agency는 정답을 맞히는 것을 넘어, 목표를 설정하고 무엇을 탐색할지 결정하는 자율성을 요구한다. 우리는 이를 <em>investigatory intelligence</em>라고 부르며, 단지 할당된 작업만 수행하는 <em>executional intelligence</em>와 구분한다. Data Science는 실제 분석이 명시적 query가 아니라 원시 데이터에서 시작된다는 점에서 자연스러운 testbed이지만, 이를 중심으로 한 benchmark는 거의 없다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 LLM이 database에서 핵심 통찰을 자율적으로 추출하는 open-ended task인 <strong>Deep Data Research (DDR)</strong>와, 검증 가능한 평가를 가능하게 하는 대규모 checklist-based benchmark인 <strong>DDR-Bench</strong>를 소개한다. 결과는 frontier model이 emergent agency를 보이지만, 장기 호라이즌 탐색은 여전히 어렵다는 점을 보여준다. 우리의 분석은 효과적인 investigatory intelligence가 agent scaffolding이나 단순한 scaling에만 의존하는 것이 아니라, agentic model의 내재적 전략에도 달려 있음을 강조한다.</p>"},{"id":"61114","en":"SetPO: Set-Level Policy Optimization for Diversity-Preserving LLM Reasoning","ko":"SetPO: 다양성을 보존하는 LLM 추론을 위한 Set-Level Policy Optimization","authors":"Chenyi Li, Yuan Zhang, Bo Wang, Guoqing Ma, Wei Tang, Haoyang Huang, Nan Duan","pos":"#113","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=tYKGzVE1g7","abs":"<p>Reinforcement learning with verifiable rewards has shown notable effectiveness in enhancing large language models (LLMs) reasoning performance, especially in mathematics tasks. However, such improvements often come with reduced outcome diversity, where the model concentrates probability mass on a narrow set of solutions. Motivated by diminishing-returns principles, we introduce a set level diversity objective defined over sampled trajectories using kernelized similarity. Our approach derives a leave-one-out marginal contribution for each sampled trajectory and integrates this objective as a plug-in advantage shaping term for policy optimization. We further investigate the contribution of a single trajectory to language model diversity within a distribution perturbation framework. This analysis theoretically confirms a monotonicity property, proving that rarer trajectories yield consistently higher marginal contributions to the global diversity. Extensive experiments across a range of model scales demonstrate the effectiveness of our proposed algorithm, consistently outperforming strong baselines in both Pass@1 and Pass@K across various benchmarks.</p>","absKo":"<p>verifiable rewards를 사용한 reinforcement learning은 large language models (LLMs)의 reasoning performance를 향상시키는 데에서 특히 mathematics task에서 괄목할 만한 효과를 보여 왔다. 그러나 이러한 향상은 종종 outcome diversity의 감소를 동반하며, 모델이 확률 질량을 소수의 해답에 집중시키게 된다. diminishing-returns 원리에 동기부여를 받아, 우리는 kernelized similarity를 사용해 sampled trajectories 위에서 정의되는 set-level diversity objective를 도입한다. 우리의 접근법은 각 sampled trajectory에 대해 leave-one-out marginal contribution을 도출하고, 이를 policy optimization을 위한 plug-in advantage shaping term으로 통합한다. 또한 distribution perturbation framework를 통해 단일 trajectory가 language model diversity에 기여하는 바를 추가로 분석한다. 이 분석은 monotonicity property를 이론적으로 확인하며, 더 희귀한 trajectory일수록 global diversity에 대해 일관되게 더 큰 marginal contribution을 제공함을 증명한다. 다양한 model scale에 걸친 광범위한 실험은 제안한 algorithm의 효과를 입증하며, 여러 benchmark에서 Pass@1과 Pass@K 모두에서 강력한 baseline을 일관되게 능가한다.</p>"},{"id":"60934","en":"Toward Safe Quantization-Aware Fine-tuning: Understanding and Mitigating Safety Alignment Degradation","ko":"안전한 Quantization-Aware Fine-tuning을 향하여: Safety Alignment Degradation 이해와 완화","authors":"Yuning Yang, Guowei Peng, Xiurui Xie, Minrui Jiang, Shuang Liang, Guisong Liu","pos":"#1600","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=vF2Xhg2s31","abs":"<p>Large language models (LLMs) are increasingly adapted to downstream tasks in resource-constrained scenarios, making quantization-aware fine-tuning (QAF) a common practice for practical deployment. However, we find that quantized LLMs are substantially more vulnerable to safety alignment degradation during fine-tuning than full-precision models by interpretability analyses. In this paper, we first theoretically reveal that this vulnerability is driven by quantization errors, manifesting as an initial safety shift followed by a distorted optimization path. Based on this insight, we propose Explicit-Safety Quantization-Aware Fine-tuning (ExSQF), which effectively restores model safety while preserving downstream performance. It initializes adapters by combining quantization error with a safety matrix projection to mitigate early safety shifts, followed by post-training refinement that corrects deviations in the optimization path. Extensive experimental results show that ExSQF achieves state-of-the-art safety alignment recovery, even surpassing existing full-precision safety-aware fine-tuning baseline, while effectively preserving model performance.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large language models(LLMs)는 자원 제약이 있는 시나리오에서 downstream task에 점점 더 많이 적응되고 있으며, 이로 인해 practical deployment를 위한 quantization-aware fine-tuning(QAF)이 일반적인 관행이 되었다. 그러나 interpretability 분석을 통해, quantized LLM이 full-precision model보다 fine-tuning 동안 safety alignment degradation에 훨씬 더 취약하다는 사실을 발견했다. 본 논문에서는 먼저 이 취약성이 quantization error에 의해 유발되며, 이는 초기 safety shift 다음에 왜곡된 optimization path로 나타난다는 점을 이론적으로 밝힌다. 이러한 통찰을 바탕으로, 우리는 모델 safety를 효과적으로 복원하면서 downstream performance를 보존하는 Explicit-Safety Quantization-Aware Fine-tuning(ExSQF)을 제안한다. ExSQF는 quantization error를 safety matrix projection과 결합하여 adapter를 초기화함으로써 초기 safety shift를 완화하고, 이후 post-training refinement를 통해 optimization path의 편차를 보정한다. 광범위한 실험 결과는 ExSQF가 기존 full-precision safety-aware fine-tuning baseline을 능가하면서도 모델 성능을 효과적으로 보존하는, state-of-the-art safety alignment recovery를 달성함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"64799","en":"Universal Reasoner: A Single, Composable Plug-and-Play Reasoner for Frozen LLMs","ko":"Universal Reasoner: Frozen LLM을 위한 단일, 조합 가능한 Plug-and-Play Reasoner","authors":"Jaemin Kim, Hangeol Chang, Hyunmin Hwang, Choonghan Kim, Jong Chul YE","pos":"#1605","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=JheeAwquCb","abs":"<p>Large Language Models (LLMs) have demonstrated remarkable general capabilities, but enhancing skills such as reasoning often demands substantial computational resources and may compromise generalization. While Parameter-Efficient Fine-Tuning (PEFT) methods offer a more resource-conscious alternative, they typically require retraining for each LLM backbone due to architectural dependencies. To address these challenges, we propose Universal Reasoner (UniR)—a lightweight, composable, and plug-and-play reasoning module that can be used with larger frozen LLMs to provide specialized reasoning capabilities. Specifically, UniR decomposes the reward into a standalone reasoning module trained in a decoupled manner using verifiable rewards, effectively translating trajectory-level signals into token-level guidance. Once trained, UniR is combined with frozen LLMs at inference time by simply adding its output logits to those of the backbone. This additive structure enables modular composition: multiple UniR modules trained for different tasks can be jointly applied by summing their logits, enabling complex reasoning via composition. Furthermore, UniR demonstrates weak-to-strong generalization, where reasoning modules trained on smaller models effectively guide much larger LLMs in the same model family, and generalize across domains such as in vision language models and medical reasoning.  Experiments on mathematical reasoning and machine translation show that UniR surpasses existing fine-tuning methods.</p>"},{"id":"61520","en":"VENOMREC: Cross-Modal Interactive Poisoning for Targeted Promotion in Multimodal LLM Recommender Systems","ko":"VENOMREC: Multimodal LLM Recommender Systems에서 Targeted Promotion을 위한 Cross-Modal Interactive Poisoning","authors":"Guowei Guan, Yurong Hao, Jiaming Zhang, Tiantong Wu, Fuyao Zhang, Tianxiang Chen, Longtao Huang, Cyril Leung, Wei Yang Bryan Lim","pos":"#1607","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=pKAOO2u6Jj","abs":"<p>Multimodal large language models (MLLMs) are pushing recommender systems (RecSys) toward content-grounded retrieval and ranking via cross-modal fusion.  We find that while cross-modal consensus often mitigates conventional poisoning that manipulates interaction logs or perturbs a single modality, it also introduces a new attack surface where synchronised multimodal poisoning can reliably steer fused representations along stable semantic directions during fine-tuning. To characterise this threat, we formalise cross-modal interactive poisoning and propose VENOMREC, which performs Exposure Alignment to identify high-exposure regions in the joint embedding space and Cross-modal Interactive Perturbation to craft attention-guided coupled token–-patch edits. Experiments on three real-world multimodal datasets demonstrate that VENOMREC consistently outperforms strong baselines,  achieving 0.73 mean ER@20 and improving over the strongest baseline by +0.52 absolute ER points on average, while maintaining comparable recommendation utility.</p>","absKo":"<p>Multimodal large language models (MLLMs)는 cross-modal fusion을 통해 recommender systems (RecSys)를 content-grounded retrieval과 ranking으로 이끌고 있다. 우리는 cross-modal consensus가 interaction log를 조작하거나 단일 modality를 교란하는 기존 poisoning을 완화하는 경우가 많지만, 동시에 동기화된 multimodal poisoning이 fine-tuning 동안 fused representation을 안정적인 semantic direction으로 신뢰성 있게 유도할 수 있는 새로운 attack surface를 만든다는 점을 발견했다. 이 위협을 특성화하기 위해 우리는 cross-modal interactive poisoning을 정식화하고, joint embedding space에서 high-exposure region을 식별하는 Exposure Alignment와 attention-guided coupled token–patch edit을 구성하는 Cross-modal Interactive Perturbation을 수행하는 VENOMREC을 제안한다. 세 개의 실제 multimodal dataset에서 수행한 실험은 VENOMREC이 강력한 baseline들을 일관되게 능가하며, mean ER@20 0.73을 달성하고 strongest baseline보다 평균 +0.52 absolute ER point 향상시키면서도 추천 utility는 비슷하게 유지함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"60489","en":"Verbalized Sampling: How to Mitigate Mode Collapse and Unlock LLM Diversity","ko":"Verbalized Sampling: Mode Collapse를 완화하고 LLM 다양성을 여는 방법","authors":"Jiayi Zhang, Simon Yu, Derek Chong, Anthony Sicilia, Michael Tomz, Christopher Manning, Weiyan Shi","pos":"#1608","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=zloIrd77G5","abs":"<p>Post-training alignment often reduces LLM diversity, leading to a phenomenon known as mode collapse. Unlike prior work that attributes this effect to algorithmic limitations, we identify a fundamental, pervasive data-level driver: typicality bias in preference data, whereby annotators systematically favor familiar text as a result of well-established findings in cognitive psychology. We formalize this bias theoretically, verify it empirically on preference datasets, and show that it plays a central role in mode collapse. Motivated by this analysis, we introduce Verbalized Sampling (VS), a simple, training-free prompting strategy to circumvent mode collapse. VS prompts the model to verbalize a probability distribution over a set of responses (e.g., \"Generate 5 jokes about coffee and their corresponding probabilities\"), which relieves the pressure to produce a single \"typical\" answer. Experiments show that VS significantly improves performance across creative writing (poems, stories, jokes), social dialogue simulation, synthetic data generation, and open-ended QA, without sacrificing safety and factual accuracy. For instance, in creative writing, VS increases diversity by 1.6-2.1x compared to direct prompting. We further observe an emergent trend that more capable models benefit more from VS. In sum, our work provides a new data-centric perspective on mode collapse and a practical inference-time remedy that helps unlock pre-trained generative diversity.</p>","absKo":"<p>post-training alignment는 종종 LLM의 다양성을 감소시켜 mode collapse라고 알려진 현상을 초래한다. 이 효과를 algorithmic limitation에 기인한다고 본 기존 연구와 달리, 우리는 더 근본적이고 광범위한 데이터 수준의 원인을 식별한다. 바로 preference data에서의 typicality bias이며, 이는 annotator가 잘 확립된 cognitive psychology 연구 결과에 따라 익숙한 텍스트를 체계적으로 선호하는 현상이다. 우리는 이 bias를 이론적으로 정식화하고, preference dataset에서 이를 실증적으로 검증하며, 그것이 mode collapse에서 핵심적인 역할을 한다는 것을 보인다. 이러한 분석에 동기를 얻어 우리는 mode collapse를 우회하기 위한 간단하고 training-free한 prompting strategy인 Verbalized Sampling (VS)을 제안한다. VS는 모델이 응답 집합에 대한 probability distribution을 언어로 풀어 설명하도록 유도한다(예: \"Generate 5 jokes about coffee and their corresponding probabilities\"), 이를 통해 하나의 ``typical''한 답변을 생성해야 한다는 압박을 완화한다. 실험은 VS가 creative writing (poems, stories, jokes), social dialogue simulation, synthetic data generation, open-ended QA 전반에서 safety와 factual accuracy를 희생하지 않으면서 성능을 유의미하게 향상시킴을 보여준다. 예를 들어 creative writing에서 VS는 direct prompting에 비해 diversity를 1.6-2.1x 증가시킨다. 우리는 더 강력한 모델일수록 VS로부터 더 큰 이익을 얻는다는 emergent trend도 관찰한다. 요약하면, 우리의 연구는 mode collapse에 대한 새로운 data-centric 관점을 제시하고, pre-trained generative diversity를 끌어내는 데 도움이 되는 실용적인 inference-time remedy를 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"62599","en":"Which Heads Matter for Reasoning? RL-Guided KV Cache Compression","ko":"추론에 중요한 Head는 무엇인가: RL-Guided KV Cache Compression","authors":"Wenjie Du, Li Jiang, Keda TAO, Xue Liu, Huan Wang","pos":"#1610","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=fBRIgbTvId","abs":"<p>Reasoning large language models exhibit complex reasoning behaviors via extended chain-of-thought generation that are highly fragile to information loss during decoding, creating critical challenges for KV cache compression. Existing token-dropping methods directly disrupt reasoning chains by removing intermediate steps, while head-reallocation methods, designed for retrieval tasks, fail to preserve the heads essential for generative reasoning. However, no existing method can identify which attention heads genuinely maintain reasoning consistency and control generation termination. To address this, we propose RLKV, which uses reinforcement learning as a probe to discover which heads contribute to reasoning quality by directly optimizing their cache usage against actual generation outcomes. This discovery naturally leads to an efficient compression strategy: we allocate full KV cache to reasoning-critical heads while aggressively compressing others. Experiments reveal that a fraction of heads proves essential for reasoning, enabling 20--50% cache reduction with near-lossless performance and up to 1.21x speedup.</p>","absKo":"<p>Reasoning large language model은 긴 chain-of-thought 생성을 통해 복잡한 추론 행동을 보이지만, decoding 중 정보 손실에 매우 취약하여 KV cache compression에 중대한 도전 과제를 제시한다. 기존 token-dropping 방법은 중간 단계를 제거함으로써 reasoning chain을 직접적으로 교란하고, retrieval task를 위해 설계된 head-reallocation 방법은 generative reasoning에 필수적인 head를 보존하지 못한다. 그러나 어떤 attention head가 실제로 reasoning consistency를 유지하고 generation termination을 제어하는지 식별할 수 있는 기존 방법은 없다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 reinforcement learning을 probe로 사용하여 실제 generation 결과에 대해 cache 사용량을 직접 최적화함으로써 어떤 head가 reasoning quality에 기여하는지 발견하는 RLKV를 제안한다. 이 발견은 자연스럽게 효율적인 compression 전략으로 이어진다. 우리는 reasoning에 결정적인 head에는 full KV cache를 할당하고, 다른 head는 공격적으로 압축한다. 실험은 일부 head만이 reasoning에 필수적임을 보여주며, 이를 통해 거의 손실 없는 성능으로 20--50% cache reduction과 최대 1.21x speedup을 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"63535","en":"WorldTravel: A Realistic Multimodal Travel-Planning Benchmark with Tightly Coupled Constraints","ko":"WorldTravel: 강하게 결합된 제약을 갖는 현실적인 멀티모달 여행 계획 벤치마크","authors":"Zexuan Wang, Chenghao Yang, Yingqi Que, Zhoufutu Wen, Zaiyuan Wang, Jiashuo Liu, Zhixin Yao, Zhenzhu Yang, Huaqing Yuan, Yiwen Wang, Zhengxuan Jiang, Shengjie Fang, Zhenhe Wu, Zhaohui Wang, JinCheng Ren, Yuzhen Li, YangYang, Jiaheng Liu, Jian Yang, Ge Zhang, Wenhao Huang","pos":"#1612","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=WKelJRz5kG","abs":"Real-world autonomous planning requires coordinating tightly coupled constraints where a single decision dictates the feasibility of all subsequent actions.  However, existing benchmarks predominantly feature loosely coupled constraints solvable through local greedy decisions and rely on idealized data, failing to capture the complexity of extracting parameters from dynamic web environments.  We introduce $\\textbf{WorldTravel}$, a benchmark comprising 150 real-world travel scenarios across 5 cities that demand navigating an average of 15+ interdependent temporal and logical constraints.  To evaluate agents in realistic deployments, we develop $\\textbf{WorldTravel-Webscape}$, a multi-modal environment featuring over 2,000 rendered webpages where agents must perceive constraint parameters directly from visual layouts to inform their planning.  Our evaluation of 10 frontier models reveals a significant performance collapse: even the state-of-the-art GPT-5.2 achieves only 28.0\\% feasibility in text-only settings, which plummets to 3.4\\% in multi-modal environments.  We identify a critical Perception-Action Gap and a Planning Horizon threshold at approximately 10 constraints where model reasoning consistently fails, suggesting that perception and reasoning remain independent bottlenecks.  These findings underscore the need for next-generation agents that unify high-fidelity visual perception with long-horizon reasoning to handle brittle real-world logistics.","absKo":"실세계 autonomous planning은 하나의 결정이 이후 모든 행동의 실현 가능성을 좌우하는, 긴밀하게 결합된 constraints를 조율해야 한다. 그러나 기존 benchmark는 대체로 local greedy decision으로 풀 수 있는 느슨하게 결합된 constraints를 다루거나 이상화된 데이터에 의존하여, dynamic web environments에서 parameters를 추출하는 복잡성을 포착하지 못한다. 우리는 5개 도시에서 150개의 실제 여행 시나리오로 구성되며, 평균 15개 이상의 상호의존적인 temporal and logical constraints를 탐색해야 하는 benchmark인 $\\textbf{WorldTravel}$을 소개한다. 현실적인 배포 환경에서 agent를 평가하기 위해, 우리는 agent가 계획 수립에 필요한 constraint parameters를 visual layouts로부터 직접 인식해야 하는 2,000개 이상의 렌더링된 webpages를 포함하는 multi-modal environment인 $\\textbf{WorldTravel-Webscape}$을 개발했다. 10개의 frontier models에 대한 평가는 심각한 성능 붕괴를 보여준다. state-of-the-art GPT-5.2조차 text-only settings에서 feasibility가 28.0\\%에 그쳤고, multi-modal environments에서는 3.4\\%까지 급락했다. 우리는 약 10개의 constraints 부근에서 model reasoning이 일관되게 실패하는 결정적 Perception-Action Gap과 Planning Horizon threshold를 확인했으며, 이는 perception과 reasoning이 여전히 독립적인 bottleneck임을 시사한다. 이러한 결과는 취약한 real-world logistics를 다루기 위해 high-fidelity visual perception과 long-horizon reasoning을 통합하는 차세대 agents의 필요성을 강조한다.</p>"},{"id":"63328","en":"T-POP: Test-Time Personalization with Online Preference Feedback","ko":"T-POP: 온라인 선호도 피드백을 활용한 테스트타임 개인화","authors":"Zikun Qu, Min Zhang, Mingze Kong, Xiang Li, Zhiwei Shang, Zhiyong Wang, Yikun Ban, Shuang Qiu, Yao Shu, Zhongxiang Dai","pos":"#1705","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Y3tTG28OO9","abs":"<p>Personalizing large language models (LLMs) to individual user preferences is a critical step beyond generating generically helpful responses. However, current personalization methods are ill-suited for new users, as they typically require either slow, resource-intensive fine-tuning or a substantial amount of pre-existing user data, creating a significant cold-start problem. To address this challenge, we introduce a new paradigm for real-time personalization by learning from online pairwise preference feedback collected during text generation. We propose T-POP (Test-Time Personalization with Online Preference Feedback), a novel algorithm that synergistically combines test-time alignment with dueling bandits. Without updating the LLM parameters, T-POP steers the decoding process of a frozen LLM by learning a reward function online that captures user preferences. By leveraging dueling bandits, T-POP intelligently queries the user to efficiently balance between exploring their preferences and exploiting the learned knowledge to generate personalized text. Extensive experiments demonstrate that T-POP achieves rapid and data-efficient personalization, significantly outperforming existing baselines and showing consistent improvement with more user interactions.</p>","absKo":"<p>대규모 언어 모델(LLM)을 개별 사용자 선호에 맞게 personalization하는 것은, 일반적으로 유용한 응답을 생성하는 단계를 넘어서는 중요한 과제이다. 그러나 현재의 personalization 방법은 새로운 사용자에게 적합하지 않다. 일반적으로 느리고 자원 소모가 큰 fine-tuning이 필요하거나, 상당한 양의 사전 사용자 데이터가 필요하기 때문에 심각한 cold-start 문제가 발생한다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 text generation 동안 수집되는 online pairwise preference feedback으로부터 학습하는 real-time personalization의 새로운 paradigm을 제안한다. 우리는 T-POP(Test-Time Personalization with Online Preference Feedback)을 제안한다. 이는 test-time alignment와 dueling bandits를 시너지 있게 결합한 새로운 알고리즘이다. LLM parameter를 업데이트하지 않고도, T-POP은 user preference를 포착하는 reward function을 online으로 학습하여 frozen LLM의 decoding process를 조정한다. Dueling bandits를 활용함으로써, T-POP은 사용자의 선호를 탐색하는 것과 학습된 지식을 활용해 개인화된 text를 생성하는 것 사이의 균형을 효율적으로 맞추도록 사용자에게 지능적으로 질의한다. 광범위한 실험 결과, T-POP은 빠르고 데이터 효율적인 personalization을 달성하며, 기존 baseline을 크게 능가하고 더 많은 사용자 상호작용에 따라 일관되게 성능이 향상됨을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"61782","en":"Star Elastic: Many-in-One Reasoning LLMs with Efficient Budget Control","ko":"Star Elastic: 효율적인 Budget Control을 갖춘 Many-in-One Reasoning LLM","authors":"Ali Taghibakhshi, Ruisi Cai, Saurav Muralidharan, Sharath Turuvekere Sreenivas, Ameya Mahabaleshwarkar, Marcin Chochowski, Akhiad Bercovich, Ran Zilberstein, Ran El-Yaniv, Yonatan Geifman, Daniel Korzekwa, Yoshi Suhara, Oluwatobi Olabiyi, Ashwath Aithal, Nima Tajbakhsh, Pavlo Molchanov","pos":"#1707","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=n1fQYnj30I","abs":"<p>Training a family of large language models (LLMs), either from scratch or via iterative compression, is prohibitively expensive and inefficient, requiring separate training runs for each model in the family. In this paper, we introduce Star Elastic, a novel LLM post-training method that adds N nested submodels to a given parent reasoning model using the compute of one run (Nx savings) via a single post-training job. Beyond reducing training costs, Star Elastic also addresses a fundamental limitation in efficient reasoning: the rigidity of static architectures, which forces the allocation of constant resources regardless of token difficulty. By unlocking elastic budget control, Star Elastic enables a novel approach that uses different submodels for each reasoning phase (thinking and answering). Star Elastic supports (1) nesting along the SSM, embedding channel, MoE and FFN axes, (2) learning nested submodels via an end-to-end trainable router, and (3) curriculum-based knowledge distillation. We apply Star Elastic to the NVIDIA Nemotron Nano models; in particular, we demonstrate its effectiveness on hybrid MoE architectures with Nemotron Nano v3 (30B/3.6A), generating 23B (2.8A) and 12B (2.0A) variants with 160B training tokens. For Nemotron Nano v2 (12B), we produce 9B and 6B nested models using only 110B training tokens, achieving a 360x reduction versus training from scratch and a 7x reduction over state-of-the-art compression methods. All nested models match or outperform independently trained baselines of comparable size. Crucially, elastic budget control advances the accuracy--latency Pareto frontier, achieving up to 16% higher accuracy and 1.9x lower latency via dynamic per-phase model selection.</p>","absKo":"<p>대규모 언어 모델(LLM) 패밀리를 scratch에서 학습하거나 iterative compression을 통해 학습하는 것은 지나치게 비용이 크고 비효율적이며, 패밀리 내 각 모델마다 별도의 training run이 필요하다. 이 논문에서는 Star Elastic을 소개한다. 이는 하나의 post-training job으로 단일 run의 compute만 사용하여 주어진 parent reasoning model에 N개의 nested submodel을 추가하는 새로운 LLM post-training method이다(Nx savings). 학습 비용을 줄이는 것을 넘어, Star Elastic은 efficient reasoning의 근본적 한계인 static architecture의 경직성도 해결한다. static architecture는 token difficulty와 무관하게 항상 동일한 자원을 할당하도록 강제한다. elastic budget control을 가능하게 함으로써, Star Elastic은 reasoning phase(think와 answer)에 따라 서로 다른 submodel을 사용하는 새로운 접근을 가능하게 한다. Star Elastic은 (1) SSM, embedding channel, MoE, FFN 축을 따라 nesting을 지원하고, (2) end-to-end trainable router를 통해 nested submodel을 학습하며, (3) curriculum-based knowledge distillation을 수행한다. 우리는 Star Elastic을 NVIDIA Nemotron Nano 모델에 적용했다. 특히 Nemotron Nano v3 (30B/3.6A)의 hybrid MoE architecture에서 그 효과를 입증했으며, 160B training token으로 23B (2.8A) 및 12B (2.0A) 변형을 생성했다. Nemotron Nano v2 (12B)에서는 110B training token만 사용해 9B 및 6B nested model을 생성했으며, scratch에서 학습하는 것 대비 360x 감소, 최신 compression method 대비 7x 감소를 달성했다. 모든 nested model은 동급 크기의 independently trained baseline과 동등하거나 그 이상을 보였다. 결정적으로, elastic budget control은 accuracy-latency Pareto frontier를 진전시켜, phase별 dynamic model selection을 통해 정확도를 최대 16% 높이고 latency를 1.9x 낮췄다.</p>"},{"id":"64987","en":"Scheduling LLM Inference with Uncertainty-Aware Output Length Predictions","ko":"불확실성 인식 출력 길이 예측을 활용한 LLM 추론 스케줄링","authors":"Haoyu Zheng, Yongqiang Zhang, Fangcheng Fu, Xiaokai Zhou, Hao Luo, Hongchao Zhu, Yuanyuan Zhu, Hao Wang, Xiao Yan, Jiawei Jiang","pos":"#1712","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=I5IMkvVKd7","abs":"To schedule LLM inference, the \\textit{shortest job first} (SJF) principle is favorable by prioritizing requests with short output lengths to avoid head-of-line (HOL) blocking. Existing methods usually predict a single output length for each request to facilitate scheduling. We argue that such a \\textit{point estimate} does not match the \\textit{stochastic} decoding process of LLM inference, where output length is \\textit{uncertain} by nature and determined by when the end-of-sequence (EOS) token is sampled. Hence, the output length of each request should be fitted with a distribution rather than a single value. With an in-depth analysis of empirical data and the stochastic decoding process, we observe that  output length follows a heavy-tailed distribution and can be fitted with the log-t distribution. On this basis, we propose a simple metric called Tail Inflated Expectation (TIE) to replace the output length in SJF scheduling, which adjusts the expectation of a log-t distribution with its tail probabilities to account for the risk that a request generates long outputs. To evaluate our TIE scheduler, we compare it with three strong baselines, and the results show that TIE reduces the per-token latency by $2.31\\times$ for online inference and improves throughput by $1.42\\times$ for offline data generation."},{"id":"60668","en":"Random Selection Reveals Implicit Knowledge Consensus in Code Generation","ko":"무작위 선택은 코드 생성에서 암묵적 지식 합의를 드러낸다","authors":"Ren-Biao Liu, Li Xin-Ye, Hui Sun, Yali Du, Jiang-Tian Xue, Ming Li","pos":"#1812","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=xpA2SBvm4g","abs":"<p>Training large language models for code generation requires selecting high-quality data from solution pools where each problem admits multiple correct implementations. Conventional studies on data selection hold that sophisticated strategies that employ various optimization objectives, such as diversity maximization or difficulty ranking, should outperform naive random sampling. However, research on <em>whether sophisticated selection methods truly benefit code generation</em> remains limited. In this work, we systematically evaluate multiple selection strategies across different representation spaces, including continuous embeddings, discrete tokens, and syntactic structures, using various base language models. We observe counterintuitive phenomena, suggesting that sophisticated methods may not yield robust benefits. Instead, simple random sampling achieves consistently competitive performance across all models, exhibiting greater stability and transferability than sophisticated methods. We attribute that an <em>implicit knowledge consensus</em> exists among diverse correct solutions, such that random selection already covers the common algorithmic knowledge required for training. Our findings provide practical insights into data selection for code generation, suggesting practitioners can adopt simple random sampling without sacrificing performance.</p>","absKo":"코드 생성을 위한 large language model을 학습하려면, 각 문제에 대해 여러 정답 구현이 존재하는 solution pool에서 고품질 데이터를 선택해야 한다. 기존의 data selection 연구는 diversity maximization이나 difficulty ranking 같은 다양한 optimization objective를 사용하는 정교한 전략이 naive random sampling보다 우수해야 한다고 본다. 그러나 <em>정교한 selection method가 실제로 code generation에 이점을 주는지</em>에 대한 연구는 여전히 제한적이다. 본 연구에서는 continuous embedding, discrete token, syntactic structure를 포함한 서로 다른 representation space와 다양한 base language model 전반에서 여러 selection strategy를 체계적으로 평가한다. 우리는 직관에 반하는 현상을 관찰했으며, 이는 정교한 방법이 견고한 이점을 제공하지 못할 수 있음을 시사한다. 그 대신 단순한 random sampling이 모든 model에서 일관되게 경쟁력 있는 성능을 보였고, 정교한 방법보다 더 높은 안정성과 전이성을 보였다. 우리는 서로 다른 정답 solution들 사이에 <em>implicit knowledge consensus</em>가 존재하여, random selection만으로도 학습에 필요한 공통 algorithmic knowledge를 이미 충분히 포괄한다고 해석한다. 우리의 결과는 code generation을 위한 data selection에 실용적인 통찰을 제공하며, 수행자들이 성능 저하 없이 단순한 random sampling을 채택할 수 있음을 시사한다.</p>"},{"id":"64423","en":"Reasoning Is Not Free: Robust Adaptive Cost-Efficient Router for LLM-as-a-Judge","ko":"추론은 공짜가 아니다: LLM-as-a-Judge를 위한 강건하고 적응적이며 비용 효율적인 라우터","authors":"Wenbo Zhang, Lijinghua Zhang, Liner Xiang, Hengrui Cai","pos":"#1813","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=NoP2UQymHU","abs":"<p>Reasoning-capable large language models (LLMs) have recently been adopted as automated judges, but their benefits and costs in LLM-as-a-Judge settings remain unclear. Through controlled comparisons between reasoning and non-reasoning judges, we show that explicit reasoning substantially improves judgment accuracy on tasks requiring structured verification (e.g., math and coding), while offering limited or even negative gains on simpler evaluations and incurring significantly higher computational cost. These findings motivate that reasoning should be used selectively rather than universally, with awareness of possible distribution shift. We propose a Robust Adaptive Cost-Efficient Router (RACER), which dynamically selects between reasoning and non-reasoning judges under a fixed budget by formulating routing as a constrained distributionally robust optimization problem. RACER explicitly accounts for distribution shift via a KL-divergence uncertainty set, admits an efficient primal–dual algorithm, and enjoys theoretical guarantees including uniqueness of the optimal policy and linear convergence. Extensive experiments show that RACER achieves superior accuracy–cost trade-offs under distribution shift.</p>","absKo":"reasoning-capable large language model(LLM)은 최근 automated judge로 채택되고 있지만, LLM-as-a-Judge 설정에서 그 이점과 비용은 아직 명확하지 않다. reasoning judge와 non-reasoning judge를 통제된 방식으로 비교한 결과, 명시적 reasoning은 구조화된 검증이 필요한 작업(예: 수학 및 코딩)에서 판단 정확도를 크게 향상시키는 반면, 더 단순한 평가에서는 이득이 제한적이거나 오히려 부정적이며, 계산 비용은 훨씬 더 높다는 것을 보였다. 이러한 결과는 reasoning을 보편적으로 적용하기보다 선택적으로 사용해야 하며, distribution shift의 가능성을 인식해야 함을 시사한다. 우리는 고정된 예산 하에서 routing을 constrained distributionally robust optimization problem으로 정식화하여 reasoning judge와 non-reasoning judge 사이를 동적으로 선택하는 Robust Adaptive Cost-Efficient Router(RACER)를 제안한다. RACER는 KL-divergence uncertainty set을 통해 distribution shift를 명시적으로 고려하고, 효율적인 primal–dual algorithm을 허용하며, 최적 정책의 유일성과 선형 수렴을 포함한 이론적 보장을 제공한다. 광범위한 실험은 RACER가 distribution shift 하에서 더 우수한 정확도–비용 trade-off를 달성함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"63724","en":"Power-Calibrated LLM Watermarking: A Statistical Framework","ko":"Power-Calibrated LLM Watermarking: 통계적 프레임워크","authors":"Xiaopu Wang, Zelin He, Chengyuan Liu, Runze Li","pos":"#1900","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=UGbAjDMxnk","abs":"<p>Logit-based watermarking is a widely used mechanism for identifying LLM generated content, yet its effectiveness is governed by a fundamental trade-off between detectability and semantic distortion. Existing analyses provide limited guidance for principled hyperparameter selection, leaving practical deployments reliant on heuristic tuning. In this work, we develop a power-calibrated statistical framework that establishes explicit quantitative relationships between watermark hyperparameters, detection power, and distortion. This characterization transforms watermark design into a guided optimization problem. Building on these results, we derive practical parameter selection procedures that achieve optimal trade-offs under constraints. Extensive experiments across multiple language models and datasets validate the theory and demonstrate that the proposed framework consistently identifies Pareto-optimal points.</p>","absKo":"<p>Logit-based watermarking은 LLM이 생성한 콘텐츠를 식별하는 데 널리 사용되는 메커니즘이지만, 그 효과는 detectability와 semantic distortion 사이의 근본적인 trade-off에 의해 좌우된다. 기존 분석은 원리적인 hyperparameter 선택에 대해 제한적인 가이지만을 제공하여, 실제 배포에서는 휴리스틱한 튜닝에 의존할 수밖에 없었다. 본 연구에서는 watermark hyperparameter, detection power, 그리고 distortion 사이의 명시적 정량 관계를 확립하는 power-calibrated statistical framework를 개발한다. 이러한 특성화는 watermark 설계를 guided optimization problem으로 변환한다. 이 결과를 바탕으로, 우리는 제약 조건 하에서 최적의 trade-off를 달성하는 실용적인 parameter selection 절차를 도출한다. 여러 language model과 dataset에 걸친 광범위한 실험은 이 이론을 검증하고, 제안한 framework가 일관되게 Pareto-optimal point를 식별함을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"62488","en":"Generalized Correctness Models: Learning Calibrated and Cross-Model Correctness Predictors from Historical Patterns","ko":"Generalized Correctness Models: 역사적 패턴으로 보정된 교차 모델 Correctness 예측기 학습","authors":"Hanqi Xiao, Vaidehi Patil, Hyunji Lee, Elias Stengel-Eskin, Mohit Bansal","pos":"#2003","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=g9G7qyAzki","abs":"<p>Generating accurate and calibrated confidence estimates is critical for deploying LLMs in high-stakes or user-facing applications, and remains an open challenge. Prior research has often framed confidence as a problem of eliciting a model’s “self-knowledge”, i.e., the ability of an LLM to judge whether its own answers are correct; this approach implicitly assumes that there is some privileged information about the answer’s correctness that is accessible to the model itself. However, we find that whether trained or training-free, an LLM attempting to predict the correctness of its own outputs generally performs no better than an unrelated LLM attempting the same task. Moreover, we hypothesize that a key factor in predicting model correctness, i.e., building a “Correctness Model” (CM), is exposure to a target model’s historical predictions. We propose multiple methods to inject this historical correctness information, including training an LLM to predict the confidences of many other LLMs, i.e., creating a Generalized Correctness Model (GCM). We use GCMs and CMs as a lens for studying the source of correctness prediction ability and its generalization, studying the importance of answer phrasing, world-knowledge, performance history, in-context examples, and posthoc-calibration for correctness prediction. We evaluate GCMs based on Qwen3-8B across 5 model families and the MMLU and TriviaQA datasets, as well as on a downstream selective prediction task, finding that reliable LLM confidence estimation is a generalizable and cross-model skill learned by systematically encoding correctness history rather than a model-specific skill reliant on introspection.</p>","absKo":"<p>정확하고 보정된 confidence estimate를 생성하는 것은 고위험 또는 사용자 대면 애플리케이션에 LLM을 배포하는 데 있어 매우 중요하지만, 여전히 해결되지 않은 과제이다. 기존 연구는 종종 confidence를 모델의 “self-knowledge”, 즉 LLM이 자신의 답이 정답인지 판단하는 능력을 끌어내는 문제로 프레이밍해 왔으며, 이 접근은 암묵적으로 모델 자신이 답의 정답 여부에 관한 특권적 정보를 접근할 수 있다는 가정을 둔다. 그러나 우리는 학습 여부와 관계없이, 자신의 출력을 예측하려는 LLM은 대체로 무관한 다른 LLM이 같은 작업을 수행하는 것보다 더 나은 성능을 보이지 않는다는 사실을 발견했다. 또한 우리는 모델 correctness를 예측하는 핵심 요인, 즉 “Correctness Model” (CM)을 구축하는 데 있어 타깃 모델의 historical prediction에 대한 노출이 중요하다고 가정한다. 우리는 많은 다른 LLM의 confidence를 예측하도록 LLM을 학습시키는 것, 즉 Generalized Correctness Model (GCM)을 만드는 방법을 포함해 이러한 historical correctness information을 주입하는 여러 방법을 제안한다. 우리는 GCM과 CM을 correctness prediction 능력의 근원과 generalization을 연구하는 렌즈로 사용하며, answer phrasing, world-knowledge, performance history, in-context example, posthoc-calibration이 correctness prediction에 미치는 중요성을 분석한다. 우리는 Qwen3-8B 기반 GCM을 5개 model family와 MMLU 및 TriviaQA dataset, 그리고 downstream selective prediction task에서 평가한 결과, 신뢰할 수 있는 LLM confidence estimation은 introspection에 의존하는 모델 고유 능력이 아니라 correctness history를 체계적으로 인코딩함으로써 학습되는, 일반화 가능하고 모델 간에 공유되는 기술임을 확인했다.</p>"},{"id":"61163","en":"How do LLMs Compute Verbal Confidence?","ko":"LLM은 언어적 Confidence를 어떻게 계산하는가?","authors":"Dharshan Kumaran, Arthur Conmy, Federico Barbero, Simon Osindero, Viorica Patraucean, Petar Veličković","pos":"#2006","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=t7oQT3uX66","abs":"<p>Verbal confidence—prompting LLMs to state their confidence as a number or category—is widely used to extract uncertainty estimates from black-box models. However, how LLMs internally generate such scores remains unknown. We address two questions: first, when confidence is computed -- just-in-time when requested, or automatically during answer generation and cached for later retrieval; and second, what verbal confidence represents -- token log-probabilities, or a richer evaluation of answer quality? Focusing on Gemma 3 27B and Qwen 2.5 7B, we provide convergent evidence for cached retrieval. Activation steering, patching, noising, and swap experiments reveal that confidence representations emerge at answer-adjacent positions before appearing at the verbalization site. Attention blocking pinpoints the information flow: confidence is gathered from answer tokens, cached at the first post-answer position, then retrieved for output. Critically, linear probing and variance partitioning reveal that these cached representations explain substantial variance in verbal confidence beyond token log-probabilities, suggesting a richer answer-quality evaluation rather than a simple fluency readout. These findings demonstrate that verbal confidence reflects automatic, sophisticated self-evaluation—not post-hoc reconstruction—with implications for understanding metacognition in LLMs and improving calibration.</p>","absKo":"<p>Verbal confidence, 즉 LLM이 자신의 confidence를 숫자나 범주로 표현하도록 유도하는 방식은 black-box model에서 uncertainty estimate를 추출하는 데 널리 사용된다. 그러나 LLM이 내부적으로 이러한 score를 어떻게 생성하는지는 알려져 있지 않다. 우리는 두 가지 질문에 답하고자 한다. 첫째, confidence는 요청받았을 때 just-in-time으로 계산되는가, 아니면 answer generation 중 자동으로 계산되어 나중에 retrieval하기 위해 cache되는가. 둘째, verbal confidence는 token log-probability를 의미하는가, 아니면 답변 품질에 대한 더 풍부한 평가를 의미하는가. Gemma 3 27B와 Qwen 2.5 7B에 초점을 맞춰, 우리는 cached retrieval에 대한 수렴하는 증거를 제시한다. activation steering, patching, noising, swap 실험은 confidence representation이 verbalization site에 나타나기 전에 answer-adjacent position에서 먼저 형성됨을 보여준다. attention blocking은 정보 흐름을 정확히 지적한다. 즉, confidence는 answer token에서 수집되고, 첫 번째 post-answer position에 cache된 뒤, 출력 시 retrieval된다. 결정적으로, linear probing과 variance partitioning은 이러한 cached representation이 token log-probability를 넘어 verbal confidence의 상당한 분산을 설명함을 보여주며, 단순한 fluency readout이 아니라 더 풍부한 answer-quality evaluation을 시사한다. 이러한 결과는 verbal confidence가 사후적 재구성이 아니라 자동적이고 정교한 self-evaluation을 반영함을 보여주며, LLM의 metacognition 이해와 calibration 개선에 시사점을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"64083","en":"Knowing When to Quit: A Principled Framework for Dynamic Abstention in LLM Reasoning","ko":"언제 멈춰야 하는지 알기: LLM 추론에서 동적 기권을 위한 원칙적 프레임워크","authors":"Hen Davidov, Nachshon Cohen, Oren Kalinsky, Yaron Fairstein, Guy Kushilevitz, Ram Yazdi, Patrick Rebeschini","pos":"#2010","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=R4fBnrKf3h","abs":"<p>Large language models (LLMs) using chain-of-thought reasoning often waste substantial compute by producing long, incorrect responses. Abstention can mitigate this by withholding outputs unlikely to be correct. While most abstention methods decide to withhold outputs before or after generation, dynamic mid-generation abstention considers early termination of unpromising reasoning traces at each token position. Prior work has explored empirical variants of this idea, but principled guidance for the abstention rule remains lacking. We present a formal analysis of dynamic abstention for LLMs, modeling abstention as an explicit action within a regularized reinforcement learning framework. An abstention reward parameter controls the trade-off between compute and information. We show that abstaining when the value function falls below this reward strictly outperforms natural baselines under general conditions. We further derive a principled and efficient method to approximate the value function. Empirical results on mathematical reasoning tasks support our theory and demonstrate improved selective accuracy over existing methods.</p>","absKo":"<p>chain-of-thought reasoning을 사용하는 large language model(LLM)은 긴데도 틀린 응답을 생성하면서 상당한 compute를 낭비하는 경우가 많다. Abstention은 정답일 가능성이 낮은 출력을 보류함으로써 이를 완화할 수 있다. 대부분의 abstention 방법이 생성 전이나 후에 출력을 보류할지를 결정하는 반면, dynamic mid-generation abstention은 각 token 위치에서 유망하지 않은 reasoning trace를 조기 종료하는 것을 고려한다. 기존 연구는 이 아이디어의 실증적 변형을 탐구했지만, abstention rule에 대한 원칙적인 지침은 여전히 부족하다. 본 논문에서는 regularized reinforcement learning framework 내에서 abstention을 명시적 action으로 모델링하여 LLM에 대한 dynamic abstention을 형식적으로 분석한다. abstention reward parameter는 compute와 information 사이의 trade-off를 제어한다. 우리는 value function이 이 reward 아래로 떨어질 때 abstain하는 것이 일반적인 조건에서 자연스러운 baseline보다 엄격하게 우수함을 보인다. 또한 value function을 근사하기 위한 원칙적이고 효율적인 방법도 도출한다. 수학적 reasoning task에서의 실험 결과는 우리의 이론을 뒷받침하며, 기존 방법보다 향상된 selective accuracy를 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"62257","en":"Empty Shelves or Lost Keys? Recall Is the Bottleneck for Parametric Factuality","ko":"빈 선반인가, 분실한 키인가? Parametric Factuality의 병목은 Recall","authors":"Nitay Calderon, Eyal Ben-David, Zorik Gekhman, Eran Ofek, Gal Yona","pos":"#2103","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=iGLpZo89xJ","abs":"<p>Standard factuality evaluations of LLMs treat all errors alike, obscuring whether failures arise from missing knowledge (empty shelves) or from limited access to encoded facts (lost keys). We propose a behavioral framework that profiles factual knowledge at the level of facts rather than questions, characterizing each fact by whether it is encoded, and then by how accessible it is: cannot be recalled, can be directly recalled, or can only be recalled with inference-time computation (thinking). To support such profiling, we introduce WikiProfile, a new benchmark constructed via an automated pipeline with a prompted LLM grounded in web search. Across 4 million responses from 13 LLMs, we find that encoding is nearly saturated in frontier models on our benchmark, with GPT-5 and Gemini-3 encoding 95--98\\% of facts. However, recall remains a major bottleneck: many errors previously attributed to missing knowledge instead stem from failures to access it. These failures are systematic and disproportionately affect long-tail facts and reverse questions. Finally, we show that thinking improves recall and can recover a substantial fraction of failures, indicating that future gains may rely less on scaling and more on methods that improve how models utilize what they already encode.</p>","absKo":"<p>LLM의 표준 factuality evaluation은 모든 오류를 동일하게 취급해, 실패가 지식의 부재(empty shelves) 때문인지 아니면 인코딩된 사실에 대한 접근 제한(lost keys) 때문인지 구분하지 못한다. 우리는 질문 단위가 아니라 fact 단위에서 factual knowledge를 프로파일링하는 behavioral framework를 제안한다. 이 프레임워크는 각 fact가 인코딩되어 있는지, 그리고 그 접근 가능성이 어떠한지에 따라 fact를 특성화한다. 즉, recall할 수 없는지, 직접 recall 가능한지, 또는 inference-time computation(thinking)을 통해서만 recall 가능한지를 구분한다. 이러한 프로파일링을 지원하기 위해, 우리는 web search에 기반해 prompt된 LLM을 사용한 automated pipeline으로 구성한 새로운 benchmark WikiProfile을 도입한다. 13개의 LLM으로부터 얻은 4백만 개의 응답 전반에서, 우리는 우리 benchmark에서 frontier model의 encoding이 거의 포화 상태임을 발견했으며, GPT-5와 Gemini-3는 사실의 95--98\\%를 인코딩한다. 그러나 recall은 여전히 큰 병목이다. 이전에는 missing knowledge로 돌려졌던 많은 오류가 실제로는 그것에 접근하지 못해서 발생한다. 이러한 실패는 체계적이며 long-tail fact와 reverse question에 불균형적으로 영향을 미친다. 마지막으로, thinking이 recall을 개선하고 실패의 상당 부분을 복구할 수 있음을 보이며, 향후 성능 향상은 scaling보다 모델이 이미 인코딩한 내용을 얼마나 잘 활용하는지 개선하는 방법에 더 크게 의존할 수 있음을 시사한다.</p>"},{"id":"64657","en":"Data Difficulty and the Generalization–Extrapolation Tradeoff in LLM Fine-Tuning","ko":"데이터 난이도와 LLM Fine-Tuning에서의 일반화-외삽 트레이드오프","authors":"Siyuan Liu, Tinghong Chen, Xinghan Li, Yifei Wang, Jingzhao Zhang","pos":"#2108","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=LCosvYhXvi","abs":"<p>Data selection during supervised fine-tuning (SFT) can critically change the behavior of large language models (LLMs).  Although existing work has studied the effect of selecting data based on heuristics such as perplexity, difficulty, or length, the reported findings are often inconsistent or context-dependent. In this work, we systematically study the role of data difficulty in fine-tuning from both empirical and theoretical perspectives, and find that there is no universally optimal difficulty level; rather, its effectiveness depends on the dataset size. We show that for a fixed data budget, there exists an optimal data difficulty for SFT, and that this optimal difficulty shifts toward harder data as the data budget increases. To explain this phenomenon, we conduct controlled synthetic experiments that reveal a simple underlying mechanism: the interplay between the (in-distribution) generalization gap and the extrapolation gap. We further support this mechanism through a theoretical analysis using PAC-Bayesian generalization bounds. Overall, our results clarify how data size and difficulty jointly affect the trade-off between generalization and extrapolation in SFT, providing guidance for difficulty-based data selection under certain model and data conditions.</p>","absKo":"<p>supervised fine-tuning (SFT) 동안의 data selection은 large language models (LLMs)의 동작을 결정적으로 바꿀 수 있다. 기존 연구들은 perplexity, difficulty, length와 같은 heuristic에 기반해 데이터를 선택하는 효과를 살펴보았지만, 보고된 결과는 종종 일관되지 않거나 문맥에 의존적이었다. 본 연구에서는 data difficulty가 fine-tuning에 미치는 역할을 실증적 및 이론적 관점에서 체계적으로 분석하고, 보편적으로 최적인 difficulty level은 존재하지 않으며, 그 효과는 dataset size에 따라 달라진다는 사실을 발견한다. 우리는 고정된 data budget에서 SFT를 위한 최적의 data difficulty가 존재하며, data budget이 증가할수록 이 최적 difficulty가 더 어려운 데이터 쪽으로 이동함을 보인다. 이 현상을 설명하기 위해, 우리는 (in-distribution) generalization gap과 extrapolation gap의 상호작용이라는 단순한 기저 메커니즘을 드러내는 통제된 synthetic experiments를 수행한다. 또한 PAC-Bayesian generalization bounds를 사용한 이론적 분석으로 이 메커니즘을 뒷받침한다. 전반적으로, 우리의 결과는 data size와 difficulty가 SFT에서 generalization과 extrapolation 사이의 trade-off에 어떻게 공동으로 영향을 미치는지 명확히 하며, 특정 model 및 data 조건에서 difficulty-based data selection에 대한 지침을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"62136","en":"Concept Heterogeneity-aware Representation Steering","ko":"개념 이질성 인식 Representation Steering","authors":"Laziz Abdullaev, Noelle Y. L. Wong, Ryan Lee, Shiqi Jiang, Minh-Khoi Nguyen-Nhat, Tan Nguyen","pos":"#2114","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=jV8qIG3xMR","abs":"<p>Representation steering offers a lightweight mechanism for controlling the behavior of large language models (LLMs) by intervening on internal activations at inference time. Most existing methods rely on a single global steering direction, typically obtained via difference-in-means over contrastive datasets. This approach implicitly assumes that the target concept is homogeneously represented across the embedding space. In practice, however, LLM representations can be highly non-homogeneous, exhibiting clustered, context-dependent structure, which renders global steering directions brittle. In this work, we view representation steering through the lens of optimal transport (OT), noting that standard difference-in-means steering implicitly corresponds to the OT map between two unimodal Gaussian distributions with identical covariance, yielding a global translation. To relax this restrictive assumption, we theoretically model source and target representations as Gaussian mixture models and formulate steering as a discrete OT problem between semantic latent clusters. From the resulting transport plan, we derive an explicit, input-dependent steering map via barycentric projection, producing a smooth, kernel-weighted combination of cluster-level shifts. We term this method Concept Heterogeneity-aware Representation Steering (CHaRS). Through numerous experimental settings, we show that CHaRS yields more effective behavioral control than global steering.</p>","absKo":"<p>Representation steering은 inference time에 내부 activation에 개입함으로써 large language model(LLM)의 동작을 제어하는 경량 메커니즘을 제공한다. 기존 방법의 대부분은 대조 데이터셋에서 difference-in-means로 얻은 단일 global steering direction에 의존한다. 이 접근은 타깃 개념이 embedding space 전반에 걸쳐 균질하게 표현된다는 가정을 암묵적으로 따른다. 그러나 실제로 LLM representation은 매우 비균질적일 수 있으며, 군집화된 context-dependent 구조를 보여 global steering direction이 쉽게 불안정해진다. 본 연구에서는 representation steering을 optimal transport(OT)의 관점에서 바라본다. 표준 difference-in-means steering이 동일한 covariance를 갖는 두 개의 unimodal Gaussian distribution 사이의 OT map에 대응하며, 결과적으로 global translation을 생성한다는 점에 주목한다. 이 제한적인 가정을 완화하기 위해, 우리는 source와 target representation을 Gaussian mixture model로 이론적으로 모델링하고, semantic latent cluster 사이의 discrete OT 문제로 steering을 정식화한다. 여기서 얻은 transport plan으로부터 barycentric projection을 통해 입력 의존적 steering map을 명시적으로 도출하며, 이는 cluster 수준 shift의 부드럽고 kernel-weighted한 결합을 생성한다. 우리는 이 방법을 Concept Heterogeneity-aware Representation Steering(CHaRS)이라 부른다. 다양한 실험 설정에서 CHaRS가 global steering보다 더 효과적인 behavioral control을 제공함을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"65161","en":"An Information-Theoretic Criterion for Efficient Data Synthesis","ko":"효율적 데이터 합성을 위한 정보 이론적 기준","authors":"Zhengqi Sun, Hanyu Li, Xiaotie Deng","pos":"#2205","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=GEKbKCTzuV","abs":"<p>Synthetic data becomes crucial for large language model training, but its effectiveness is highly inconsistent. Here we provide an information-theoretic understanding of such inconsistency. Synthetic data is effective only when the generation-training loop is information-open: it has continuous information injections by external signals (verifiers, environments, or rubrics) that supply task-relevant signal not implied by the model's current probability distribution. When the loop is information-closed and relies mainly on self-generated samples, repeated processing tends to degrade performance. Based on this criterion, we further study factors that influence the efficiency of information injections by different synthetic methods. We argue that information-efficient methods often lead to strong generalization, which relies on simple, unified signals that ignore nuisance variation across examples, rather than adding more instance-level labels. Our work thus provides an operational guide for designing and understanding synthetic data methods, echoing Sutton's \"bitter lesson\" -- that compute-scalable, general methods ultimately beat human-built structure in the long run.</p>"},{"id":"64992","en":"Bridging the Knowledge-Prediction Gap in LLMs on Multiple-Choice Questions","ko":"객관식 문제에서 LLM의 지식-예측 간극 연결","authors":"Yoonah Park, Haesung Pyun, Yohan Jo","pos":"#2209","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=I0RgZXTO53","abs":"<p>While large language models (LLMs) perform strongly on diverse tasks, their trustworthiness is limited by erratic behavior that is unfaithful to their internal knowledge. In particular, LLMs often fail on multiple-choice questions (MCQs) even if they encode correct answers in their hidden representations, revealing a misalignment between internal knowledge and output behavior. We investigate and mitigate this knowledge-prediction gap on MCQs through a three-step analysis of hidden representations. First, we quantify the prevalence and magnitude of the gap across models and datasets. Second, we provide a geometric interpretation by identifying distinct knowledge and prediction subspaces in the residual stream. Third, we introduce KAPPA, a lightweight inference-time intervention that aligns the two subspaces within the residual stream to reduce the knowledge-prediction gap. Our results provide a geometric and interpretable explanation of the knowledge-prediction gap in LLMs. Furthermore, KAPPA effectively reduces the gap across diverse MCQ benchmarks and models, and generalizes to free-form settings.</p>"},{"id":"61651","en":"Beyond Correctness: Distance-Based Social Dynamics of Multi-Agent Debate","ko":"정답을 넘어: Multi-Agent Debate의 거리 기반 사회적 동역학","authors":"Seungwoong Ha, Melanie Mitchell","pos":"#305","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=o4v0sr8Mpy","abs":"<p>Multi-agent debate (MAD) systems are often evaluated using binary correctness or peer agreement, yet such evaluations obscure how individual agents revise their answers during social interaction. We study the microscopic dynamics of answer revision in large language models (LLMs) using ConceptARC, a 2D grid-reasoning benchmark that admits quantitative distance measures between candidate solutions. By exposing a target model to controlled configurations of peer answers, we analyze how revision likelihood and direction depend on both social context and the distance between answers and the ground truth. We find that agents are more likely to revise when their answers are farther from the correct solution, and that revisions of incorrect answers exhibit a systematic contraction toward the ground truth, even when the final answer remains incorrect. Conversely, correct answers can be overturned by social pressure, particularly when wrong peers are near-correct. Together, these results show that multi-agent interaction induces structured, distance-aware movements in solution space that are invisible under binary correctness, clarifying when social reasoning leads to improvement, stability, or gradual regression in solution quality.</p>","absKo":"<p>multi-agent debate(MAD) 시스템은 종종 binary correctness나 peer agreement를 사용해 평가되지만, 이러한 평가는 사회적 상호작용 동안 개별 agent가 자신의 답을 어떻게 수정하는지를 가린다. 우리는 후보 solution 간의 정량적 거리 측정을 허용하는 2D grid-reasoning benchmark인 ConceptARC를 사용해, large language model(LLM)에서 answer revision의 미시적 동역학을 연구한다. target model에 peer answer의 제어된 구성을 노출함으로써, 우리는 revision 가능성과 방향이 사회적 맥락과 답과 ground truth 사이의 거리에 어떻게 의존하는지 분석한다. 우리는 agent가 자신의 답이 정답에서 더 멀수록 수정할 가능성이 더 높고, 잘못된 답의 수정은 최종 답이 여전히 틀리더라도 ground truth를 향해 체계적으로 수축하는 경향이 있음을 발견한다. 반대로, 특히 틀린 peer가 거의 정답에 가까울 때는 사회적 압력에 의해 정답이 뒤집힐 수 있다. 종합하면, 이러한 결과는 multi-agent 상호작용이 이진 정답 여부로는 보이지 않는, solution space에서 구조화되고 거리 인지적인 이동을 유도함을 보여주며, 사회적 추론이 solution quality의 향상, 안정성, 또는 점진적 퇴행으로 이어지는 시점을 명확히 한다.</p>"},{"id":"65681","en":"Safety Anchor: Defending Harmful Fine-tuning via Geometric Bottlenecks","ko":"Safety Anchor: 기하학적 병목을 통한 유해 파인튜닝 방어","authors":"Guoxin Lu, Letian Sha, Qing Wang, Peijie Sun, Hao Zhou, Hua Dai, Fu Xiao","pos":"#3105","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=BDR6RK9TmA","abs":"The safety alignment of Large Language Models (LLMs) remains vulnerable to Harmful Fine-tuning (HFT). While existing defenses impose constraints on parameters, gradients, or internal representations, we observe that they can be effectively circumvented under persistent HFT. Our analysis traces this failure to the inherent redundancy of the high-dimensional parameter space: attackers exploit optimization trajectories that are orthogonal to defense constraints to restore harmful capabilities while deceptively adhering to safety restrictions.    To address this, we propose Safety Bottleneck Regularization (SBR). SBR shifts the defensive focus from the redundant parameter space to the unembedding layer, which serves as a geometric bottleneck. By anchoring the final hidden states of harmful queries to those of the safety-aligned model, SBR enables the model to maintain safe responses even under persistent HFT. Extensive experiments confirm SBR's effectiveness, demonstrating that utilizing just a single safety anchor is sufficient to reduce the Harmful Score to $&lt;$10 while preserving competitive performance on benign downstream tasks. The code is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/SBR-F876"},{"id":"65557","en":"Beyond Fixed Biases: Decoding the Role of Reasoning Uncertainty in MLLM Modality Conflicts","ko":"고정된 편향을 넘어서: MLLM 모달리티 충돌에서 추론 불확실성의 역할 해독","authors":"Zhuoran Zhang, Tengyue Wang, Xilin Gong, Yang Shi, Haotian Wang, Di Wang, Lijie Hu","pos":"#3314","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=CQtHecicN0","abs":"<p>Multimodal Large Language Models (MLLMs) must resolve conflicts when modalities provide contradictory information, a process we term \"modality following\". We propose a framework that deconstructs this behavior into case-specific relative reasoning uncertainty and a model's stable inherent preference. By evaluating diverse MLLMs, we establish a universal law: the probability of following a modality decreases monotonically as its relative reasoning uncertainty increases, which is robustly preserved across diverse uncertainty indices. This law allows us to quantify a \"balance point\" where uncertainties are subjectiveized, offering a principled measure of modality bias that is disentangled from unimodal capabilities. Probing the internal decision-making reveals that this conflict resolution is a high-level cognitive process: in ambiguous regions near the balance point, models exhibit significant \"concept oscillations,\" where top predictions vacillate between modalities specifically within the middle-to-late layers. Finally, we demonstrate the framework's utility for preference steering through Supervised Fine-Tuning (SFT). We find that data efficiency is governed by reasoning uncertainty: training on easy samples (where one modality dominates) fails to generalize, whereas targeting the identified ``boundary cases\" is essential for robust preference alignment and suppressing internal vacillation.</p>"},{"id":"62172","en":"Scheduling Thoughts: Learning the Order of Thought in Diffusion Language Models","ko":"Scheduling Thoughts: Diffusion Language Models에서 Thought 순서 학습","authors":"Jiawei Xu, Minghui Liu, Aakriti Agrawal, Yifan Chen, Furong Huang","pos":"#3401","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=j4UhHaxCpq","abs":"Masked diffusion language models decode by iteratively unmasking tokens, where the unmasking order defines an ``order of thought''  that strongly influences generation quality yet is typically chosen heuristically.  We derive a tractable upper bound on the sequential decoding mismatch, measured by the Kullback–Leibler divergence and expressed in terms of the model’s pathwise log-likelihood, with tightness under sufficient model expressivity.  This bound induces a dense self-aware reward for a target sequence $x$ and unmasking order $\\sigma$,  over ordered paths, casting order selection as a principled policy optimization problem with a frozen denoiser.  We instantiate this idea as **Self-Aware Scheduling (SAS)**, which learns a lightweight order policy using Group Relative Policy Optimization and applies seamlessly to both sequential and semi-autoregressive decoding.  On Sudoku with 1B MDM, SAS improves puzzle accuracy from $82.0\\%$ (best heuristic schedule) to $91.8\\%$, and reaches $97.9\\%$ with second-stage fine-tuning along learned trajectories.  On LLaDA-8B, SAS improves pass@1 on GSM8K from $64\\%$ to $76\\%$ (full diffusion) and on MBPP from $39.5\\%$ to $41\\%$, while consistently matching or exceeding heuristic schedules across generation lengths and block sizes.","absKo":"Masked diffusion language models는 토큰을 반복적으로 unmask하며 decode하는데, 이때 unmasking order는 generation quality에 강하게 영향을 주는 ``order of thought''를 정의하지만, 보통 heuristic으로 선택된다. 우리는 sequential decoding mismatch에 대한 tractable한 upper bound를 유도한다. 이는 Kullback–Leibler divergence로 측정되며, model의 pathwise log-likelihood로 표현되고, 충분한 model expressivity 하에서 tight함을 보인다. 이 bound는 target sequence $x$와 unmasking order $\\sigma$에 대해 ordered paths 위의 dense한 self-aware reward를 유도하여, order selection을 frozen denoiser를 사용하는 principled policy optimization problem으로 재정식화한다. 우리는 이 아이디어를 **Self-Aware Scheduling (SAS)**으로 구현하며, Group Relative Policy Optimization을 사용해 lightweight order policy를 학습하고 sequential 및 semi-autoregressive decoding 모두에 seamless하게 적용한다. Sudoku에서 1B MDM을 사용했을 때, SAS는 puzzle accuracy를 $82.0\\%$ (best heuristic schedule)에서 $91.8\\%$로 향상시키고, learned trajectory를 따라 second-stage fine-tuning을 하면 $97.9\\%$에 도달한다. LLaDA-8B에서는 SAS가 GSM8K의 pass@1을 $64\\%$에서 $76\\%$로, MBPP의 pass@1을 $39.5\\%$에서 $41\\%$로 개선하며, generation length와 block size 전반에서 heuristic schedule과 일관되게 같거나 더 나은 성능을 보인다."},{"id":"61711","en":"DeepImageSearch: Benchmarking Multimodal Agents for Context-Aware Image Retrieval in Visual Histories","ko":"DeepImageSearch: 시각적 히스토리에서 맥락 인식 이미지 검색을 위한 멀티모달 Agent 벤치마킹","authors":"Chenlong Deng, Mengjie Deng, Junjie Wu, Dun Zeng, Teng Wang, Qingsong Xie, Jiadeng Huang, Shengjie Ma, Changwang Zhang, Zhaoxiang Wang, Jun Wang, Yutao Zhu, Zhicheng Dou","pos":"#3412","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=nZ5kjt0Qla","abs":"<p>Existing multimodal retrieval systems excel at semantic matching but implicitly assume that query-image relevance can be measured in isolation. This paradigm overlooks the rich dependencies inherent in realistic visual streams, where information is distributed across temporal sequences rather than confined to single snapshots. To bridge this gap, we introduce DeepImageSearch, a novel agentic paradigm that reformulates image retrieval as an autonomous exploration task. Models must plan and perform multi-step reasoning over raw visual histories to locate targets based on implicit contextual cues. We construct DISBench, a challenging benchmark built on interconnected visual data. To address the scalability challenge of creating context-dependent queries, we propose a human-model collaborative pipeline that employs vision-language models to mine latent spatiotemporal associations, effectively offloading intensive context discovery before human verification. Furthermore, we build a robust baseline using a modular agent framework equipped with fine-grained tools and a dual-memory system for long-horizon navigation. Extensive experiments demonstrate that DISBench poses significant challenges to state-of-the-art models, highlighting the necessity of incorporating agentic reasoning into next-generation retrieval systems.</p>","absKo":"기존 multimodal retrieval system은 semantic matching에는 뛰어나지만, query-image relevance가 고립된 상태에서 측정될 수 있다고 암묵적으로 가정한다. 이 패러다임은 실제 visual stream에 내재한 풍부한 의존성을 간과하는데, 정보가 단일 snapshot에 국한되지 않고 temporal sequence 전반에 분산되어 있기 때문이다. 이 간극을 메우기 위해, 우리는 image retrieval을 자율 탐색(task)으로 재정의하는 새로운 agentic paradigm인 DeepImageSearch를 제안한다. 모델은 암묵적인 contextual cue를 바탕으로 target을 찾기 위해 raw visual history에 대해 multi-step reasoning을 계획하고 수행해야 한다. 우리는 상호 연결된 visual data를 기반으로 한 도전적인 benchmark인 DISBench를 구축한다. context-dependent query를 만드는 데 따른 확장성 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 vision-language model을 사용해 잠재적인 spatiotemporal association을 탐색하는 human-model collaborative pipeline을 제안하며, 이를 통해 human verification 이전의 intensive context discovery를 효과적으로 오프로딩한다. 또한, 정교한 tools와 장기 navigation을 위한 dual-memory system을 갖춘 modular agent framework로 강력한 baseline을 구축한다. 광범위한 실험은 DISBench가 최신 모델들에게 상당한 도전 과제를 제시하며, 차세대 retrieval system에 agentic reasoning을 통합할 필요성을 강조함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"63635","en":"Causal Direct Preference Optimization for Distributionally Robust Generative Recommendation","ko":"분포적으로 강인한 생성 추천을 위한 인과적 직접 선호 최적화","authors":"Chu Zhao, Enneng Yang, Jianzhe Zhao, Guibing Guo","pos":"#3911","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=VDaJ5RCOh4","abs":"<p>Direct Preference Optimization (DPO) guides large language models (LLMs) to generate recommendations aligned with user historical behavior distributions by minimizing preference alignment loss. However, our systematic empirical research and theoretical analysis reveal that DPO tends to amplify spurious correlations caused by environmental confounders during the alignment process, significantly undermining the generalization capability of LLM-based generative recommendation methods in out-of-distribution (OOD) scenarios. To mitigate this issue, we propose CausalDPO, an extension of DPO that incorporates a causal invariance learning mechanism. This method introduces a backdoor adjustment strategy during the preference alignment phase to eliminate interference from environmental confounders, explicitly models the latent environmental distribution using a soft clustering approach, and enhances robust consistency across diverse environments through invariance constraints. Theoretical analysis demonstrates that CausalDPO can effectively capture users' stable preference structures across multiple environments, thereby improving the OOD generalization performance of LLM-based recommendation models. We conduct extensive experiments under four representative distribution shift settings to validate the effectiveness of CausalDPO, achieving an average performance improvement of 24.10\\% across four evaluation metrics.</p>","absKo":"Direct Preference Optimization (DPO)는 preference alignment loss를 최소화함으로써 large language models (LLMs)가 사용자 과거 행동 분포와 정렬된 recommendation을 생성하도록 유도한다. 그러나 우리의 체계적인 실증 연구와 이론 분석은 DPO가 정렬 과정에서 환경 교란변수로 인해 발생하는 허위 상관을 증폭시키는 경향이 있으며, 그 결과 out-of-distribution (OOD) 시나리오에서 LLM 기반 생성형 추천 방법의 일반화 능력이 크게 저하됨을 보여준다. 이 문제를 완화하기 위해, 우리는 causal invariance learning mechanism을 통합한 DPO의 확장판인 CausalDPO를 제안한다. 이 방법은 preference alignment 단계에서 environmental confounder의 간섭을 제거하기 위한 backdoor adjustment strategy를 도입하고, soft clustering approach를 사용해 잠재 환경 분포를 명시적으로 모델링하며, invariance constraint를 통해 다양한 환경 전반에서 robust consistency를 강화한다. 이론 분석은 CausalDPO가 여러 환경에 걸친 사용자들의 안정적인 preference structure를 효과적으로 포착하여, LLM 기반 추천 모델의 OOD 일반화 성능을 향상시킬 수 있음을 보여준다. 우리는 네 가지 대표적인 distribution shift 설정에서 광범위한 실험을 수행하여 CausalDPO의 효과를 검증했으며, 네 가지 평가 지표에서 평균 24.10\\%의 성능 향상을 달성했다.</p>"},{"id":"64117","en":"SafeSpec: Fast and Safe LLM via Dynamic Reflective Sampling","ko":"SafeSpec: 동적 반영 샘플링을 통한 빠르고 안전한 LLM","authors":"HAOTIAN XU, Zeyang Zhang, Linbao Li, Huadi Zheng, YU LI, Cheng Zhuo","pos":"#3915","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=QlNI5wckx0","abs":"<p>Speculative inference accelerates large language model (LLM) decoding but provides no inherent safety guarantees. Existing safety defenses are largely incompatible with speculative inference: they either introduce additional computation or disrupt the draft–verify mechanism, negating acceleration benefits. This reveals a fundamental incompatibility between current safety methods and speculative decoding. We propose SafeSpec, a safety-aware speculative inference framework that integrates risk estimation directly into the verification process. SafeSpec attaches a lightweight latent safety head to the target model to jointly evaluate semantic validity and safety in a single forward pass. When unsafe generations are detected, SafeSpec applies rollback and safety-guided reflective multi-sampling to recover safe continuations rather than terminating generation. We model jailbreak attacks as distributional shifts over generative trajectories, where adversarial prompts increase the probability of harmful continuations without eliminating safe ones. Under this model, SafeSpec performs risk-aware trajectory recovery within the speculative decoding process. Across multiple models and adversarial benchmarks, SafeSpec achieves a substantially improved safety–efficiency trade-off. On Qwen3-32B, SafeSpec reduces attack success rates by 15\\% while preserving a 2.06× inference speedup, demonstrating that speculative acceleration and inference-time safety can be jointly optimized.</p>","absKo":"<p>Speculative inference는 large language model(LLM) 디코딩을 가속하지만, 본질적인 safety 보장은 제공하지 않는다. 기존의 safety 방어 기법들은 대체로 speculative inference와 양립하지 않는데, 추가 계산을 유발하거나 draft–verify 메커니즘을 교란하여 가속 이점을 상쇄하기 때문이다. 이는 현재의 safety 방법과 speculative decoding 사이에 근본적인 비양립성이 있음을 보여준다. 우리는 risk estimation을 verification 과정에 직접 통합하는 safety-aware speculative inference 프레임워크인 SafeSpec를 제안한다. SafeSpec는 target model에 경량 latent safety head를 부착하여 단일 forward pass에서 semantic validity와 safety를 함께 평가한다. unsafe generation이 감지되면, SafeSpec는 생성을 종료하는 대신 rollback과 safety-guided reflective multi-sampling을 적용하여 안전한 continuation을 복구한다. 우리는 jailbreak attack을 generative trajectory에 대한 distributional shift로 모델링하며, adversarial prompt가 safe continuation을 제거하지 않으면서 harmful continuation의 확률을 높인다고 본다. 이 모델 하에서 SafeSpec는 speculative decoding 과정 내에서 risk-aware trajectory recovery를 수행한다. 여러 모델과 adversarial benchmark 전반에서 SafeSpec는 safety와 efficiency 사이의 trade-off를 크게 개선한다. Qwen3-32B에서는 SafeSpec가 inference speedup 2.06×를 유지하면서 attack success rate를 15\\% 줄여, speculative acceleration과 inference-time safety를 함께 최적화할 수 있음을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"66794","en":"Reward Shaping for Inference-Time Alignment: A Stackelberg Game Perspective","ko":"추론 시점 정렬을 위한 Reward Shaping: Stackelberg Game 관점","authors":"Haichuan Wang, Tao Lin, Lingkai Kong, Ce Li, Hezi Jiang, Milind Tambe","pos":"#4401","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=0FzaPyOEB7","abs":"<p>Existing alignment methods directly use the reward model learned from user preference data to optimize an LLM policy, subject to KL regularization with respect to the base policy. This practice is suboptimal for maximizing user's utility because the KL regularization may cause the LLM to inherit the bias in the base policy that conflicts with user preferences. While amplifying rewards for preferred outputs can mitigate this bias, it also increases the risk of reward hacking. This tradeoff motivates the problem of optimally designing reward models under KL regularization. We formalize this reward model optimization problem as a Stackelberg game, and show that a simple reward shaping scheme can effectively approximate the optimal reward model. We empirically evaluate our method in inference-time alignment settings and demonstrate that it integrates seamlessly into existing alignment methods with minimal overhead. Our method consistently improves average reward and achieves win–tie rates exceeding 66\\% against all baselines, averaged across evaluation settings.</p>"},{"id":"62552","en":"A model of errors in transformers","ko":"Transformer의 오차 모델","authors":"Suvrat Raju, Praneeth Kumar Netrapalli","pos":"#4612","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=fbabBXNeqw","abs":"<p>We study the error rate of LLMs on tasks like arithmetic that require a deterministic output, and repetitive processing of tokens drawn from a small set of alternatives. We argue that incorrect predictions arise when small errors in the attention mechanism accumulate to cross a threshold, and use this insight to derive a quantitative two-parameter relationship between the accuracy and the complexity of the task. The two parameters vary with the prompt and the model; they can be interpreted in terms of an elementary noise rate, and the number of plausible erroneous tokens that can be predicted. Our analysis is inspired by an \"effective field theory'' perspective: the LLM's many raw  parameters can be reorganized into just two parameters that govern the error rate.  We perform extensive empirical tests, using Gemini 2.5 Flash, Gemini 2.5 Pro and DeepSeek R1,  and find excellent agreement between the predicted and observed accuracy for a variety of tasks, although we also identify deviations in some cases.  Our model provides an alternative to suggestions that errors made by LLMs on long repetitive tasks indicate the  \"collapse of reasoning'', or an inability to express \"compositional'' functions. Finally, we show how to construct prompts to reduce the error rate.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 산술과 같이 deterministic output을 요구하고, 작은 대안 집합에서 뽑힌 token들을 반복적으로 처리해야 하는 task에서 LLM의 error rate를 연구한다. 우리는 잘못된 예측은 attention mechanism의 작은 오류가 누적되어 임계값을 넘을 때 발생한다고 주장하며, 이 통찰을 사용해 accuracy와 task complexity 사이의 정량적인 두 매개변수 관계를 도출한다. 이 두 매개변수는 prompt와 model에 따라 달라지며, elementary noise rate와 예측 가능한 plausible erroneous token의 개수라는 관점에서 해석할 수 있다. 우리의 분석은 \"effective field theory\" 관점에서 영감을 받았다. LLM의 많은 원시 parameter를 error rate를 지배하는 두 개의 parameter로 재구성할 수 있다는 것이다. 우리는 Gemini 2.5 Flash, Gemini 2.5 Pro, DeepSeek R1을 사용해 광범위한 실험적 검증을 수행했으며, 다양한 task에서 예측된 정확도와 관측된 정확도 사이에 매우 잘 맞는 일치를 확인했다. 다만 일부 경우에는 편차도 발견했다. 우리의 모델은 LLM이 긴 반복 task에서 범하는 오류가 \"collapse of reasoning\" 또는 \"compositional\" function을 표현할 수 없다는 징후라는 주장에 대한 대안적 설명을 제공한다. 마지막으로, error rate를 줄이기 위한 prompt 구성 방법을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"66581","en":"Break the Block: Dynamic-size Reasoning Blocks for Diffusion Large Language Models via Monotonic Entropy Descent with Reinforcement Learning","ko":"블록을 깨라: 강화 학습을 통한 단조 엔트로피 하강으로 Diffusion 대규모 언어 모델을 위한 동적 크기 추론 블록","authors":"Yan Jiang, Ruihong Qiu, Zi Huang","pos":"#2208","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=2SUX04aKod","abs":"<p>Recent diffusion large language models (dLLMs) have demonstrated both effectiveness and efficiency in reasoning via a block-based semi-autoregressive generation paradigm. Despite their progress, the fixed-size block generations remain a critical bottleneck for effective and coherent reasoning. (I) From a global perspective, different reasoning tasks would correspond to different optimal decoding block sizes, which makes a \"one-size-fits-all\" assumption ineffective. (II) Even within a single reasoning task, the rigid block partitioning would break the logical flow and reduce reasoning coherence. Through empirical observations, we reveal that, for block-wise entropy, incorrect reasoning exhibits a fluctuating and unsteady trend between blocks, while the correctly generated tasks follow a consistent descending paradigm. Therefore, this paper proposes b1, a novel post-training framework that learns dynamic-size reasoning blocks via a Monotonic Entropy Descent objective with reinforcement learning to enhance reasoning coherence. b1 integrates seamlessly as a plug-and-play module with existing dLLM's post-training algorithms. Extensive experiments across various reasoning benchmarks showcase b1's consistent improvement over fixed-size block baselines. Our code has been provided.</p>"},{"id":"61192","en":"CoPE: Continual Probe-guided Expansion for Large Vision-Language Models","ko":"CoPE: Large Vision-Language Model을 위한 Continual Probe-guided Expansion","authors":"Ziqin Wang, Hengyuan Zhao, Qixin Sun, Yilin Li, Kaiyou Song, Xiaolin Hu, Qingpei Guo, Linjiang Huang, Si Liu","pos":"#4603","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ssUgzVTtkB","abs":"<p>Mixture of Experts architectures have recently advanced the scalability and adaptability of Large Language Models for continual multimodal learning. However, extending these models to accommodate sequential tasks remains challenging.  As new tasks arrive, naive model expansion leads to rapid parameter growth, while modifying shared routing components often causes catastrophic forgetting, undermining previously learned knowledge. To address these issues, we propose CoPE, a continual learning framework for LLMs that requires no replay data of previous tasks and ensures both parameter efficiency and robust knowledge retention. Our approach introduces the Probe-Guided Knowledge Extension mechanism, which uses probe experts to dynamically determine when and where new experts should be added, enabling adaptive and minimal parameter expansion tailored to task complexity. To support inference without task labels, we further incorporate a Probabilistic Task Locator that dynamically matches inputs to the correct task-specific components.  To handle the practical issue that task labels are unknown during inference, we leverage a VAE-based reconstruction strategy to identify the most suitable router by matching input distributions, allowing automatic and accurate expert allocation. This design mitigates routing conflicts and catastrophic forgetting, enabling robust continual learning without explicit task labels. Extensive experiments on the CoIN benchmark, covering eight diverse VQA tasks, demonstrate that CoPE delivers strong continual learning performance with a compact model size, significantly reducing forgetting and parameter overhead compared to prior methods. These results showcase the effectiveness and scalability of our approach for parameter-efficient continual learning in large language models. Our code will be open-sourced soon.</p>","absKo":"<p>Mixture of Experts architecture는 최근 연속적 multimodal learning을 위한 Large Language Models의 확장성과 적응성을 크게 발전시켰다. 그러나 이러한 모델을 sequential task에 맞게 확장하는 일은 여전히 어렵다. 새로운 task가 도착할 때, 단순한 model expansion은 parameter growth를 빠르게 유발하고, 공유 routing component를 수정하면 이미 학습한 지식을 훼손하는 catastrophic forgetting이 발생하기 쉽다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 이전 task의 replay data를 전혀 필요로 하지 않으면서 parameter 효율성과 강한 knowledge retention을 동시에 보장하는 LLM용 continual learning framework인 CoPE를 제안한다. 우리의 접근법은 Probe-Guided Knowledge Extension 메커니즘을 도입하여, probe expert를 사용해 새로운 expert를 언제 어디에 추가해야 하는지를 동적으로 결정하고, task complexity에 맞춘 적응적이면서도 최소한의 parameter expansion을 가능하게 한다. task label 없이 inference를 수행하기 위해, 우리는 입력을 올바른 task-specific component와 동적으로 매칭하는 Probabilistic Task Locator도 추가로 통합한다. inference 시 task label이 알려지지 않는 실제 문제를 처리하기 위해, 우리는 VAE 기반 reconstruction strategy를 활용하여 input distribution을 맞춰 가장 적합한 router를 식별하고, 이를 통해 자동적이고 정확한 expert allocation을 가능하게 한다. 이 설계는 routing conflict와 catastrophic forgetting을 완화하여, 명시적 task label 없이도 강건한 continual learning을 가능하게 한다. 서로 다른 8개의 VQA task를 포함하는 CoIN benchmark에서 수행한 광범위한 실험은, CoPE가 compact한 model size로도 강력한 continual learning 성능을 제공하며, 기존 방법들에 비해 forgetting과 parameter overhead를 크게 줄인다는 것을 보여준다. 이러한 결과는 large language model에서 parameter-efficient continual learning을 위한 우리의 접근법의 효과성과 확장성을 입증한다. 우리의 코드는 곧 공개될 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"61082","en":"Spurious Rewards: Rethinking Training Signals in RLVR","ko":"가짜 보상: RLVR의 학습 신호 재고","authors":"Rulin Shao, Stella Li, Rui Xin, Scott Geng, Yiping Wang, Sewoong Oh, Simon Du, Nathan Lambert, Sewon Min, Ranjay Krishna, Yulia Tsvetkov, Hannaneh Hajishirzi, Pang Wei Koh, Luke Zettlemoyer","pos":"#1709","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=tqTNOpkP5j","abs":"<p>We show that reinforcement learning with verifiable rewards (RLVR) can elicit strong mathematical reasoning in certain language models even with spurious rewards that have little, no, or outright negative correlation with the correct answer. For example, RLVR training with GRPO improves MATH-500 performance for Qwen2.5-Math-7B in absolute points by 21.4% using randomly assigned rewards, nearly matching the 29.1% gained with ground truth rewards. To explain this counterintuitive observation, we show that GRPO exhibits a clipping bias arising from the clip term, which can amplify high-prior behaviors learned during pre-training even without informative rewards. As a case study, we identify one such high-prior behavior for Qwen2.5-Math models, which we term code reasoning---reasoning in code without actual code execution; code reasoning frequency increases from 65% to over 90% with spurious rewards. However, the presence of such amplifiable behaviors is highly model-dependent. In practice, spurious rewards that are effective for Qwen models often fail to produce gains for other model families, such as Llama3 or OLMo2. Our results highlight the importance of validating RL methods across diverse models rather than relying on a single de facto choice: large performance gains can arise on Qwen models even from random rewards that do not reflect genuine capability improvements.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 verifiable reward를 사용하는 reinforcement learning (RLVR)이, 정답과의 상관이 거의 없거나 아예 없거나 심지어 음의 상관을 보이는 spurious reward만으로도 특정 language model에서 강한 mathematical reasoning을 유도할 수 있음을 보인다. 예를 들어, GRPO를 사용하는 RLVR training은 무작위로 할당된 reward만으로 Qwen2.5-Math-7B의 MATH-500 성능을 절대점수 기준 21.4% 향상시키며, ground truth reward로 얻는 29.1% 향상에 거의 근접한다. 이 직관에 반하는 관찰을 설명하기 위해, 우리는 GRPO가 clip term에서 기인하는 clipping bias를 보이며, 이 bias가 informative reward가 없더라도 pre-training 동안 학습된 high-prior behavior를 증폭할 수 있음을 보인다. 사례 연구로서, 우리는 Qwen2.5-Math model에서 이러한 high-prior behavior 중 하나를 식별하고 이를 code reasoning이라고 부른다. 즉, 실제 code execution 없이 code 안에서 reasoning하는 것으로, spurious reward와 함께 code reasoning 빈도는 65%에서 90% 이상으로 증가한다. 그러나 이렇게 증폭 가능한 behavior의 존재는 model에 매우 의존적이다. 실제로 Qwen model에서는 효과적이었던 spurious reward가 Llama3나 OLMo2 같은 다른 model family에서는 종종 성과 향상을 만들어내지 못한다. 우리의 결과는 단일 de facto choice에 의존하기보다 다양한 model에 걸쳐 RL method를 검증하는 것이 중요함을 강조한다. 즉, 진정한 capability 향상을 반영하지 않는 random reward만으로도 Qwen model에서 큰 성능 향상이 나타날 수 있다.</p>"},{"id":"66366","en":"REAR: Test-time Preference Realignment through Reward Decomposition","ko":"REAR: 보상 분해를 통한 테스트 시점 선호 재정렬","authors":"Fuxiang Zhang, Pengcheng Wang, Chenran Li, Yi-Chen Li, Yuxin Chen, Lang Feng, Chenfeng Xu, Masayoshi Tomizuka, Bo An","pos":"#1808","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=4KqCBOoKk7","abs":"Aligning large language models (LLMs) with diverse user preferences is a critical yet challenging task. While post-training methods can adapt models to specific needs, they often require costly data curation and additional training. Test-time scaling (TTS) presents an efficient, training-free alternative, but its application has been largely limited to verifiable domains like mathematics and coding, where response correctness is easily judged. To extend TTS to preference alignment, we introduce a novel framework that models the task as a realignment problem, since the base model often fails to sufficiently align with the stated preference. Our key insight is to decompose the underlying reward function into two components: one related to the question and the other to preference information. This allows us to derive a REAlignment Reward (REAR) that selectively rescales the proportions of these two reward terms. We then show that REAR can be formulated as a linear combination of token-level policy log-probabilities, making it computationally efficient and easy to integrate with various TTS algorithms such as best-of-$N$ sampling and tree search. Experiments show that compared to other test-time baselines, REAR not only enables scable test-time realignment for preference alignment tasks under diverse user requirements, but also generalizes to mathematical and visual tasks under appropriate preference settings."},{"id":"61517","en":"Just-In-Time Reinforcement Learning: Continual Learning in LLM Agents Without Gradient Updates","ko":"Just-In-Time Reinforcement Learning: Gradient Update 없는 LLM Agents의 Continual Learning","authors":"yibo li, Zijie Lin, Ailin Deng, Xuan (Billy) Zhang, Yufei He, Shuo Ji, Tri Cao, Bryan Hooi","pos":"#2901","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=pLvye0zHUC","abs":"<p>While Large Language Model (LLM) agents excel at general tasks, they inherently struggle with continual adaptation due to the frozen weights after deployment. Conventional reinforcement learning (RL) offers a solution but incurs prohibitive computational costs and the risk of catastrophic forgetting.      We introduce Just-In-Time Reinforcement Learning (JitRL), a training-free framework that enables test-time policy optimization without any gradient updates.      JitRL maintains a dynamic, non-parametric memory of experiences and retrieves relevant trajectories to estimate action advantages on-the-fly.      These estimates are then used to directly modulate the LLM's output logits.      We theoretically prove that this additive update rule is the exact closed-form solution to the KL-constrained policy optimization objective.      Extensive experiments on WebArena and Jericho demonstrate that JitRL establishes a new state-of-the-art among training-free methods.      Crucially, JitRL outperforms the performance of computationally expensive fine-tuning methods (e.g., WebRL) while reducing monetary costs by over 30 times, offering a scalable path for continual learning agents. The code is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/JitRL-D485.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large Language Model(LLM) agent는 일반적인 task에서는 뛰어나지만, 배포 후 frozen weight 때문에 continual adaptation에서는 본질적으로 어려움을 겪는다. Conventional reinforcement learning(RL)은 해결책을 제공하지만 막대한 계산 비용과 catastrophic forgetting의 위험을 수반한다. 우리는 gradient update 없이 test-time policy optimization을 가능하게 하는 training-free framework인 Just-In-Time Reinforcement Learning(JitRL)을 제안한다. JitRL은 경험의 동적 non-parametric memory를 유지하고, 관련 trajectory를 검색하여 action advantage를 즉시 추정한다. 이 추정치는 이후 LLM의 output logit을 직접 조절하는 데 사용된다. 우리는 이 additive update rule이 KL-constrained policy optimization objective의 정확한 closed-form solution임을 이론적으로 증명한다. WebArena와 Jericho에서의 광범위한 실험은 JitRL이 training-free method 중 새로운 state of the art를 확립함을 보여준다. 결정적으로 JitRL은 계산 비용이 큰 fine-tuning method(예: WebRL)의 성능을 능가하면서도 금전적 비용을 30배 이상 줄여, continual learning agent를 위한 확장 가능한 경로를 제공한다. 코드는 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/JitRL-D485 에서 이용 가능하다.</p>"},{"id":"63604","en":"$V_0$: A Generalist Value Model for Any Policy at State Zero","ko":"$V_0$: 상태 0에서 어떤 정책에도 적용 가능한 범용 가치 모델","authors":"Yi-Kai Zhang, Zhiyuan Yao, Hongyan Hao, Yueqing Sun, Qi GU, Hui Su, Xunliang Cai, De-Chuan Zhan, Han-Jia Ye","pos":"#3217","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=VYTU8l8WO9","abs":"Traditional value models $V^{\\pi}$ in LLM reinforcement learning face a coupling dilemma: they require synchronous training alongside the updating policy $\\pi$, causing inefficiency and overfitting. In this paper, we propose $V_0$, a generalist value model that decouples value estimation from specific policy parameters by reframing the task as in-context learning to predict performance for unseen policies. We utilize the policy's historical query-performance pairs as a capability representation, transforming from $V^{\\pi}(s_0)$ to $V(C_{\\pi}, s_0)$, where $C_{\\pi}$ serves as an in-context input. This architecture enables us to scale the diversity of policies within the training set. Consequently, $V_0$ achieves scaling in learning to rapidly identify the capability boundaries of any policy without updating its parameters. Technically, we employ a Residual Query Adapter to compress the high-dimensional policy representation and the target query into structured features, which are then processed by a pre-trained TabPFN head. Empirical results show that $V_0$ outperforms coupled value models in tracking policy evolution during GRPO training, optimizes cold-start budget allocation, and approaches the performance-cost Pareto frontier in inference routing.","absKo":"LLM reinforcement learning에서 전통적인 value model $V^{\\pi}$는 결합 딜레마에 직면한다. 즉, 업데이트되는 policy $\\pi$와 함께 동기적으로 학습되어야 하므로 비효율과 과적합이 발생한다. 본 논문에서는 특정 policy parameter와의 결합을 끊고, 보지 못한 policy에 대한 성능을 예측하는 in-context learning 문제로 재정식화한 generalist value model $V_0$를 제안한다. 우리는 policy의 과거 query-performance pair를 capability representation으로 활용하여 $V^{\\pi}(s_0)$에서 $V(C_{\\pi}, s_0)$로 변환하며, 여기서 $C_{\\pi}$는 in-context input으로 작동한다. 이러한 architecture는 training set 내 policy의 다양성을 확장할 수 있게 한다. 그 결과 $V_0$는 parameter를 업데이트하지 않고도 어떤 policy든 capability boundary를 신속하게 식별하는 능력을 학습하는 scaling을 달성한다. 기술적으로는, 고차원 policy representation과 target query를 구조화된 feature로 압축하는 Residual Query Adapter를 사용하고, 그 후 pre-trained TabPFN head가 이를 처리한다. 실험 결과 $V_0$는 GRPO 학습 동안 policy evolution을 추적하는 데 있어 coupled value model보다 우수하며, cold-start budget allocation을 최적화하고, inference routing에서 performance-cost Pareto frontier에 근접한다."},{"id":"62611","en":"Rethinking the Trust Region in LLM Reinforcement Learning","ko":"LLM Reinforcement Learning의 Trust Region 재고찰","authors":"Penghui Qi, Xiangxin Zhou, Zichen Liu, Tianyu Pang, Chao Du, Min Lin, Wee Sun Lee","pos":"#3611","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=f4g8zblbwp","abs":"<p>Reinforcement learning (RL) has become a cornerstone for fine-tuning Large Language Models (LLMs), with Proximal Policy Optimization (PPO) serving as the de facto standard algorithm. Despite its ubiquity, we argue that the core ratio clipping mechanism in PPO is structurally ill-suited for the large vocabularies inherent to LLMs. PPO constrains policy updates based on the probability ratio of sampled tokens, which serves as a noisy single-sample Monte Carlo estimate of the true policy divergence. This creates a sub-optimal learning dynamic: updates to low-probability tokens are aggressively over-penalized, while potentially catastrophic shifts in high-probability tokens are under-constrained, leading to training inefficiency and instability. To address this, we propose Divergence Proximal Policy Optimization (DPPO), which substitutes heuristic clipping with a more principled constraint based on a direct estimate of policy divergence (e.g., Total Variation or KL). To avoid huge memory footprint, we introduce the efficient Binary and Top-K approximations to capture the essential divergence with negligible overhead. Extensive empirical evaluations demonstrate that DPPO achieves superior stability and efficiency compared to existing methods, offering a more robust foundation for RL-based LLM fine-tuning.</p>","absKo":"<p>Reinforcement learning(RL)은 Large Language Models(LLMs) 미세조정의 핵심 기반이 되었으며, Proximal Policy Optimization(PPO)은 사실상의 표준 알고리즘으로 널리 사용된다. 그러나 그 보편성에도 불구하고, 우리는 PPO의 핵심적인 ratio clipping 메커니즘이 LLM에 내재된 대규모 vocabulary에 구조적으로 부적합하다고 주장한다. PPO는 샘플링된 token의 probability ratio를 기반으로 policy update를 제약하는데, 이는 실제 policy divergence의 noisy한 single-sample Monte Carlo 추정치에 해당한다. 이로 인해 최적보다 못한 학습 동역학이 발생한다. 즉, 낮은 확률 token에 대한 update는 과도하게 강한 페널티를 받는 반면, 높은 확률 token에서 발생할 수 있는 치명적인 변화는 충분히 제약되지 않아 학습 비효율과 불안정성이 초래된다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 heuristic clipping을 policy divergence의 직접 추정치(예: Total Variation 또는 KL)에 기반한 더 원리적인 제약으로 대체하는 Divergence Proximal Policy Optimization(DPPO)을 제안한다. 막대한 메모리 사용량을 피하기 위해, 우리는 중요한 divergence를 거의 추가 오버헤드 없이 포착하는 효율적인 Binary 및 Top-K approximation을 도입한다. 광범위한 실증 평가 결과, DPPO는 기존 방법들에 비해 더 뛰어난 안정성과 효율성을 달성하며, RL 기반 LLM 미세조정을 위한 더 견고한 기반을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"65850","en":"Maximizing the Spectral Energy Gain in Sub-1-Bit LLMs via Latent Geometry Alignment","ko":"잠재 기하학 정렬을 통한 Sub-1-Bit LLM의 스펙트럼 에너지 이득 최대화","authors":"Banseok Lee, Youngmin Kim","pos":"#1914","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=9TMdlXCn79","abs":"We identify the Spectral Energy Gain in extreme model compression, where low-rank binary approximations outperform tiny-rank floating-point baselines for heavy-tailed spectra. However, prior attempts fail to realize this potential, trailing state-of-the-art 1-bit methods. We attribute this degradation to Latent Geometry Misalignment: standard singular vectors exhibit high coherence (spiky distribution), the worst-case geometry for binary quantization. To realize this gain, we propose LittleBit-2, a framework employing Internal Latent Rotation and Joint Iterative Quantization (Joint-ITQ). This approach acts as a geometric preconditioner, aligning coherent latent distributions with the binary hypercube with zero inference overhead. Empirically, LittleBit-2 establishes a new state-of-the-art in the sub-1-bit regime (1$\\sim$0.1 bpp) on Llama-2 and Llama-3, matching the fidelity of leading 1-bit baselines."},{"id":"62512","en":"SubspacePath Pruner: Inference-time Pruning via Probe-based Representation–Parameter Coupling","ko":"SubspacePath Pruner: Probe 기반 Representation–Parameter 결합을 통한 추론 시 Pruning","authors":"Zhiren Gong, Yikun Hou, Fan Wu, CHE WANG, Fuyao Zhang, Tiantong Wu, Yurong Hao, Jiaming Zhang, Yiyang Duan, Tiantong Wang, Fei Huang, Chau Yuen, Wei Yang Bryan Lim","pos":"#4017","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=fvkCjFvWKf","abs":"<p>Large-scale dedicated application of LLMs in diverse scenarios increasingly demands specialized model inference behavior under strict constraints of accuracy, latency, and memory. However, the heterogeneous and long-tailed nature of real-world specialized scenarios makes it difficult to obtain training data and optimize models.  We study a practical inference-time specialization setting: given an LLM base, we compile a reusable, budget-bounded pathway/subnetwork within a specific scenario. Our approach is motivated by an empirical coupling phenomenon: input scenario sets aligned with similar representation subspaces (e.g., domain) in embedding space tend to activate a consistent and sparse set of internal reasoning pathways in model parameter space. To build the bridge between them, we propose probe-based SubspacePath Pruner with two core components: (1) Domain-Basis Synthesis (DBS) constructs a quasi-orthogonal basis of domain axes in embedding space, serving as a stable coordinate system. (2) Probe-based Scenario Pruning (PSP) uses efficient layer-wise linear probes to estimate axis alignment and compute budgeted head-wise pathways for a specific scenario. Experiments on LLaMA-2-13B show 29.3 average Recall on cross-domain tests (vs. 24.7 dense) and 21.6 on cross-dataset tests (vs. 25.5 dense) with 1.27x speedup at ~30% pruning ratio.</p>","absKo":"<p>다양한 시나리오에서 LLMs의 대규모 전용 application은 정확도, latency, memory에 대한 엄격한 제약 하에서 특화된 model inference behavior를 점점 더 요구하고 있다. 그러나 실제 특화 시나리오의 이질적이고 long-tailed한 특성 때문에 training data를 확보하고 model을 최적화하기가 어렵다. 우리는 실용적인 inference-time specialization 설정을 연구한다: 주어진 LLM base에 대해, 특정 시나리오 내에서 재사용 가능한 budget-bounded pathway/subnetwork를 구성한다. 우리의 접근은 경험적으로 관찰된 coupling 현상에서 출발한다. embedding space에서 유사한 representation subspace(예: domain)에 정렬된 input scenario set은 model parameter space에서 일관되고 sparse한 internal reasoning pathway 집합을 활성화하는 경향이 있다. 이들 사이의 다리를 놓기 위해, 우리는 두 가지 핵심 구성 요소를 갖는 probe-based SubspacePath Pruner를 제안한다. (1) Domain-Basis Synthesis (DBS)는 embedding space에서 domain axes의 quasi-orthogonal basis를 구성하여 안정적인 coordinate system 역할을 한다. (2) Probe-based Scenario Pruning (PSP)은 효율적인 layer-wise linear probe를 사용해 axis alignment를 추정하고, 특정 시나리오에 대한 budgeted head-wise pathways를 계산한다. LLaMA-2-13B에서 수행한 실험은 cross-domain test에서 평균 Recall 29.3( dense 대비 24.7 )을, cross-dataset test에서 21.6( dense 대비 25.5 )을 보였으며, 약 30% pruning ratio에서 1.27x speedup을 달성했다.</p>"},{"id":"63686","en":"Low Kruskal-Rank Adaptation","ko":"Low Kruskal-Rank 적응","authors":"Yixing Xu, Guanchen Li, Chao Li, Xuanwu Yin, Dong Li, Spandan Tiwari, Ashish Sirasao, Emad Barsoum","pos":"#2015","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=UcnpfSsXtu","abs":"Low-rank adaptation (LoRA) is one of the most widely used parameter-efficient fine-tuning (PEFT) methods for adapting pre-trained large language models (LLMs) to downstream tasks. Although LoRA significantly reduces the number of trainable parameters and lowers fine-tuning costs, its performance is often limited by the inherent low-rank assumption. In this paper, we revisit the notion of rank for LoRA update matrices and show that the standard matrix rank fails to capture duplicated directions and redundancy in the update subspace. Motivated by this analysis, we argue that the Kruskal rank offers a more informative criterion for characterizing update diversity. We therefore propose **Low Kruskal Rank Adaptation** (LoKRA), a new PEFT algorithm with provable theoretical guarantees that mitigates the limitations of LoRA. We further introduce LoKRA$^+$, an enhanced variant that provides a tighter theoretical lower bound on the Kruskal rank and yields stronger empirical performance. Experiments on multiple LLMs show that our approach consistently outperforms LoRA and other baselines, establishing state-of-the-art performance across a range of benchmarks.","absKo":"Low-rank adaptation (LoRA)는 pre-trained large language model (LLM)을 downstream task에 적응시키기 위해 가장 널리 사용되는 parameter-efficient fine-tuning (PEFT) 방법 중 하나이다. LoRA는 학습 가능한 parameter 수를 크게 줄이고 fine-tuning 비용을 낮추지만, 그 성능은 종종 내재된 low-rank 가정에 의해 제한된다. 본 논문에서는 LoRA update matrix의 rank 개념을 재검토하고, 표준 matrix rank가 update subspace 내의 중복된 방향과 redundancy를 포착하지 못함을 보인다. 이러한 분석에 동기를 얻어, 우리는 Kruskal rank가 update diversity를 특성화하는 데 더 많은 정보를 제공하는 criterion이라고 주장한다. 따라서 우리는 LoRA의 한계를 완화하는, 이론적으로 보장 가능한 새로운 PEFT algorithm인 **Low Kruskal Rank Adaptation** (LoKRA)을 제안한다. 또한 Kruskal rank에 대한 더 타이트한 이론적 lower bound를 제공하고 더 강한 empirical performance를 보이는 향상된 변형인 LoKRA$^+$를 추가로 제안한다. 여러 LLM에 대한 실험은 우리의 접근법이 LoRA와 다른 baseline을 일관되게 능가하며, 다양한 benchmark 전반에서 state-of-the-art 성능을 확립함을 보여준다."},{"id":"63791","en":"DisPPO: Quantile-Based Distributional Reinforcement Learning for Large Language Models","ko":"DisPPO: 대형 언어 모델을 위한 분위수 기반 분포형 강화학습","authors":"Zhijian Zhou, Long Li, Xuan Zhang, Zongkai Liu, Yanting Miao, Yuchen Liu, Deshu Chen, Ke Li, Xing Sun, Ruoxi Jiang, Xiaoyu Tan, Chao Qu, Yuan Qi","pos":"#123","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Tkdgg5uqNK","abs":"Reinforcement Learning (RL) has become a cornerstone for enhancing the reasoning capabilities of Large Language Models (LLMs). However, standard actor-critic methods, such as PPO, rely on scalar value functions that estimate only the expectation of cumulative returns. This reduction inherently discards higher-order statistical information (e.g., variance and multimodality), leading to inaccurate value estimation and suboptimal credit assignment in complex tasks. While Distributional RL offers a solution by modeling the full return distribution, its application to LLMs remains challenging due to the computational intractability of value-based operations over large vocabularies and the instability and memory burden of off-policy replay mechanisms. In this paper, we propose DisPPO, a novel on-policy framework that seamlessly integrates non-parametric quantile regression into PPO. Theoretically, we prove that our distributional update operator---composed of the $\\lambda$-return Bellman operator and quantile projection---is a contraction mapping in the Wasserstein metric, guaranteeing convergence to a unique fixed point. Empirically, we evaluate DisPPO using Llama and Qwen models across diverse benchmarks, including mathematical reasoning and Text-to-SQL generation. DisPPO consistently outperforms standard PPO and recent group-based baselines in both Pass@1 and Pass@$k$ metrics, demonstrating that distributional critics provide a richer, more robust learning signal for large-scale reasoning models.","absKo":"Reinforcement Learning (RL)은 Large Language Models (LLMs)의 reasoning capability를 향상시키는 핵심 축이 되었다. 그러나 PPO와 같은 표준 actor-critic 방법은 누적 return의 기댓값만을 추정하는 scalar value function에 의존한다. 이러한 축약은 분산과 multimodality와 같은 고차 통계 정보를 본질적으로 소실시켜, 복잡한 task에서 부정확한 value estimation과 비최적의 credit assignment를 초래한다. Distributional RL은 return의 전체 분포를 모델링함으로써 이러한 문제에 대한 해법을 제공하지만, 큰 vocabulary 전반에 걸친 value-based operation의 계산 비가용성과 off-policy replay mechanism이 야기하는 불안정성 및 메모리 부담 때문에 LLM에의 적용은 여전히 어렵다. 본 논문에서는 non-parametric quantile regression을 PPO에 매끄럽게 통합한 새로운 on-policy framework인 DisPPO를 제안한다. 이론적으로 우리는 $\\lambda$-return Bellman operator와 quantile projection으로 구성된 distributional update operator가 Wasserstein metric에서 contraction mapping임을 증명하여, 유일한 fixed point로의 수렴을 보장한다. 실증적으로는 수학적 추론과 Text-to-SQL generation을 포함한 다양한 benchmark에서 Llama 및 Qwen 모델을 사용해 DisPPO를 평가한다. DisPPO는 Pass@1과 Pass@$k$ 지표 모두에서 표준 PPO와 최근의 group-based baseline을 일관되게 능가하며, distributional critic이 대규모 reasoning model에 더 풍부하고 견고한 learning signal을 제공함을 보여준다."},{"id":"60858","en":"Understanding Dynamic Compute Allocation in Recurrent Transformers","ko":"Recurrent Transformer의 동적 계산 할당 이해","authors":"Ibraheem Muhammad Moosa, Suhas Lohit, Ye Wang, Moitreya Chatterjee, Wenpeng Yin","pos":"#1603","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=vzzTxg0cbU","abs":"<p>Token-level adaptive computation seeks to reduce inference cost by allocating more computation to harder tokens and less to easier ones. However, prior work is primarily evaluated on natural-language benchmarks using task-level metrics, where token-level difficulty is unobservable and confounded with architectural factors, making it unclear whether compute allocation truly aligns with underlying complexity. We address this gap through three contributions. First, we introduce a complexity-controlled evaluation paradigm using algorithmic and synthetic language tasks with parameterized difficulty, enabling direct testing of token-level compute allocation. Second, we propose ANIRA, a unified recurrent Transformer framework that supports per-token variable-depth computation while isolating compute allocation decisions from other model factors. Third, we use this framework to conduct a systematic analysis of token-level adaptive computation across alignment with complexity, generalization, and decision timing. Our results show that compute allocation aligned with task complexity can emerge without explicit difficulty supervision, but such alignment does not imply algorithmic generalization: models fail to extrapolate to unseen input sizes despite allocating additional computation. We further find that early compute decisions rely on static structural cues, whereas online halting more closely tracks algorithmic execution state.</p>","absKo":"<p>Token-level adaptive computation은 더 어려운 token에는 더 많은 computation을, 쉬운 token에는 더 적은 computation을 할당함으로써 inference cost를 줄이려는 접근이다. 그러나 기존 연구는 주로 task-level metric을 사용하는 자연어 benchmark에서 평가되며, token-level 난이도는 관찰할 수 없고 architectural factor와도 혼재되어 있다. 이로 인해 compute allocation이 실제로 underlying complexity와 정렬되는지 분명하지 않다. 우리는 세 가지 기여를 통해 이 공백을 메운다. 첫째, 우리는 parameterized difficulty를 갖는 algorithmic 및 synthetic language task를 사용하는 complexity-controlled evaluation paradigm을 도입하여 token-level compute allocation을 직접 검증할 수 있게 한다. 둘째, 우리는 compute allocation 결정을 다른 model factor로부터 분리하면서 token별 variable-depth computation을 지원하는 통합 recurrent Transformer framework인 ANIRA를 제안한다. 셋째, 우리는 이 framework를 사용하여 complexity와의 alignment, generalization, 그리고 decision timing 전반에 걸친 token-level adaptive computation을 체계적으로 분석한다. 우리의 결과는 task complexity와 정렬된 compute allocation이 명시적 difficulty supervision 없이도 나타날 수 있음을 보여주지만, 이러한 정렬이 algorithmic generalization을 의미하지는 않음을 보여준다. 모델은 추가 computation을 할당하더라도 보지 못한 input size로 외삽하지 못한다. 또한 우리는 초기 compute decision이 static structural cue에 의존하는 반면, online halting은 algorithmic execution state를 더 가깝게 추적함을 확인한다.</p>"},{"id":"61329","en":"TextResNet: Decoupling and Routing Optimization Signals in Compound AI Systems via Deep Residual Tuning","ko":"TextResNet: Deep Residual Tuning을 통한 Compound AI System의 최적화 신호 분리와 라우팅","authors":"Suizhi Huang, Mei Li, Han Yu, Xiaoxiao Li","pos":"#1702","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=rGtym1nlqZ","abs":"<p>Textual Gradient-style optimizers (TextGrad) enable gradient-like feedback propagation through compound AI systems. However, they do not work well for deep chains. The root cause of this limitation stems from the <em>Semantic Entanglement</em> problem in these extended workflows. In standard textual backpropagation, feedback signals mix local critiques with upstream contexts, leading to <em>Attribution Ambiguity</em>. To address this challenge, we propose TextResNet, a framework that reformulates the optimization process to achieve precise signal routing via four key innovations. Firstly, in the forward pass, it enforces Additive Semantic Deltas to preserve an Identity Highway for gradient flow. Secondly, in the backward pass, it introduces Semantic Gradient Decomposition via a Semantic Projector to disentangle feedback into causally independent subspaces. Thirdly, it implements Causal Routing, which routes projected signals to their specific components. Finally, it performs Density-Aware Optimization Scheduling to leverage the disentangled signals to dynamically allocate resources to key system bottlenecks. Our results show that TextResNet not only achieves superior performance compared to TextGrad, but also exhibits remarkable stability for agentic tasks in compound AI systems where baselines collapse. The code will be made public after the review.</p>","absKo":"<p>Textual Gradient 스타일 optimizer (TextGrad)는 compound AI system 전반에 gradient-like feedback propagation을 가능하게 한다. 그러나 deep chain에서는 잘 작동하지 않는다. 이러한 한계의 근본 원인은 이 확장된 workflow에서의 <em>Semantic Entanglement</em> 문제에 있다. 표준 textual backpropagation에서는 feedback signal이 local critique와 upstream context를 섞어 <em>Attribution Ambiguity</em>를 유발한다. 이 과제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 네 가지 핵심 혁신을 통해 optimization process를 정밀한 signal routing이 가능하도록 재구성한 TextResNet을 제안한다. 첫째, forward pass에서 Additive Semantic Delta를 강제하여 gradient flow를 위한 Identity Highway를 보존한다. 둘째, backward pass에서 Semantic Projector를 통한 Semantic Gradient Decomposition을 도입해 feedback을 causally independent한 subspace로 분해한다. 셋째, projected signal을 각기 구체적인 component로 전달하는 Causal Routing을 구현한다. 마지막으로, Density-Aware Optimization Scheduling을 수행하여 분해된 signal을 활용해 주요 system bottleneck에 자원을 동적으로 할당한다. 우리의 결과는 TextResNet이 TextGrad에 비해 우수한 성능을 달성할 뿐 아니라, baseline이 붕괴하는 compound AI system의 agentic task에서도 놀라운 안정성을 보임을 보여준다. 코드는 리뷰 후 공개할 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"61369","en":"Tackling Length Inflation Without Trade-offs: Group Relative Reward Rescaling for Reinforcement Learning","ko":"Trade-off 없이 Length Inflation 해결: Reinforcement Learning을 위한 Group Relative Reward Rescaling","authors":"Zichao Li, Jie Lou, Fangchen Dong, Zhiyuan Fan, Mengjie Ren, Hongyu Lin, Xianpei Han, Debing Zhang, Le Sun, Yaojie Lu, XingYu","pos":"#1704","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=quqoVYpzX3","abs":"Reinforcement learning significantly enhances LLM capabilities but suffers from a critical issue: length inflation, where models adopt verbosity or inefficient reasoning to maximize rewards.  Prior approaches struggle to address this challenge in a general and lossless manner, primarily because additive penalties introduce a compensatory effect that creates optimization shortcuts, while heuristic gating strategies lack generality beyond binary feedback. To bridge this gap, we present Group Relative Reward Rescaling (GR$^3$), which reframes length control as a multiplicative rescaling paradigm, effectively establishing a generalized, continuous, and reward-dependent gating mechanism. To further ensure lossless optimization, we incorporate group-relative regularization and advantage-aware calibration, which dynamically adapt length budgets to instance difficulty and preserve the advantage signal of high-quality trajectories. Empirically, across both RLHF and RLVR settings, GR$^3$ maintains training dynamics and downstream performance comparable to standard GRPO while significantly mitigating length inflation, outperforming state-of-the-art length-regularized baselines.","absKo":"Reinforcement learning은 LLM의 능력을 크게 향상시키지만, 길이 팽창(length inflation)이라는 치명적인 문제를 겪는다. 이는 모델이 보상을 극대화하기 위해 장황함이나 비효율적인 추론을 채택하는 현상이다. 기존 접근법은 주로 가산적 패널티가 최적화의 지름길을 만드는 보상적 효과를 유발하고, 휴리스틱 게이팅 전략은 이진 피드백을 넘어서는 일반성이 부족하기 때문에, 이 문제를 일반적이고 손실 없이 해결하는 데 어려움을 겪는다. 이러한 간극을 메우기 위해, 우리는 Group Relative Reward Rescaling (GR$^3$)를 제안한다. 이는 길이 제어를 곱셈적 재스케일링 패러다임으로 재정식화하여, 일반화 가능하고 연속적이며 reward-dependent한 게이팅 메커니즘을 효과적으로 확립한다. 손실 없는 최적화를 더욱 보장하기 위해, 우리는 group-relative regularization과 advantage-aware calibration을 도입하여, 인스턴스 난이도에 맞추어 length budget을 동적으로 조정하고 고품질 trajectory의 advantage 신호를 보존한다. 실험적으로, RLHF와 RLVR 설정 모두에서 GR$^3$는 표준 GRPO와 유사한 학습 동역학과 downstream 성능을 유지하면서도 길이 팽창을 크게 완화하며, 최신 length-regularized baseline들을 능가한다."},{"id":"65806","en":"Search or Accelerate: Confidence-Switched Position Beam Search for Diffusion Language Models","ko":"탐색할까 가속할까: Diffusion 언어 모델을 위한 신뢰도 전환 위치 빔 서치","authors":"Mingyu Cao, Alvaro Correia, Christos Louizos, Shiwei Liu, Lu Yin","pos":"#1711","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=9xxnyqiZoO","abs":"<p>Diffusion Language Models (DLMs) generate text by iteratively denoising a masked sequence, repeatedly deciding which positions to commit at each step. Standard decoding follows a greedy rule, unmasking the most confident positions, yet this local choice can lock the model into a suboptimal unmasking order, especially on reasoning-heavy prompts. We present Search Or AcceleRate (SOAR), a training-free decoding algorithm that adapts its behavior to the model’s uncertainty. When confidence is low, SOAR briefly widens the search over alternative unmasking decisions to avoid premature commitments; when confidence is high, it collapses the search and decodes many positions in parallel to reduce the number of denoising iterations. Across mathematical reasoning and code generation benchmarks (GSM8K, MBPP, HumanEval) on Dream-7B and LLaDA-8B, SOAR improves generation quality while maintaining competitive inference speed, offering a practical way to balance quality and efficiency in DLM decoding.</p>"},{"id":"60709","en":"Scaling Beyond Masked Diffusion Language Models","ko":"Masked Diffusion Language Model을 넘어서는 Scaling","authors":"Subham Sekhar Sahoo, Jean-Marie Lemercier, Zhihan Yang, Justin Deschenaux, Jingyu Liu, John Thickstun, Ante Jukić","pos":"#1713","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=xKJG1CNtQM","abs":"<p>Diffusion language models are a promising alternative to autoregressive models due to their potential for faster generation. Among discrete diffusion approaches, Masked diffusion currently dominates, largely driven by strong perplexity on language modeling benchmarks. In this work, we present the first scaling law study of Uniform-state and interpolating discrete diffusion methods. We also show that masked diffusion models can be made approximately 12% more FLOPs-efficient when trained with a simple cross-entropy objective. We find that perplexity is informative within a diffusion family but can be misleading across families, where models with worse likelihood scaling may be preferable due to faster and more practical sampling, as reflected by the speed-quality Pareto frontier. These results challenge the view that masked diffusion is categorically the future of diffusion language modeling and that perplexity alone suffices for cross-algorithm comparison. Scaling all methods to 1.7B parameters, we show that uniform-state diffusion remains competitive on likelihood-based benchmarks and outperforms autoregressive and masked diffusion models on GSM8K, despite worse validation perplexity. Overall, <strong>our results challenge the view that masked diffusion is categorically the future of diffusion language modeling</strong> and that perplexity alone suffices for cross-algorithm comparison.</p>","absKo":"<p>Diffusion language model은 더 빠른 생성 가능성 때문에 autoregressive model의 유망한 대안이다. discrete diffusion 접근법 중에서는 Masked diffusion이 현재 주류를 이루며, 이는 주로 language modeling benchmark에서의 강한 perplexity에 의해 주도된다. 본 연구에서는 Uniform-state 및 interpolating discrete diffusion method에 대한 최초의 scaling law 연구를 제시한다. 또한 단순한 cross-entropy objective로 학습할 경우 masked diffusion model이 약 12% 더 FLOPs-efficient해질 수 있음을 보인다. 우리는 perplexity가 diffusion family 내부에서는 유용하지만 family 간 비교에서는 오해를 부를 수 있으며, likelihood scaling이 더 나쁜 model이 speed-quality Pareto frontier에 반영되듯 더 빠르고 실용적인 sampling 때문에 오히려 선호될 수 있음을 발견한다. 이러한 결과는 masked diffusion이 diffusion language modeling의 미래라는 관점과, perplexity만으로 cross-algorithm comparison이 충분하다는 관점을 모두 चुनौती한다. 모든 방법을 1.7B parameter로 확장했을 때, 우리는 uniform-state diffusion이 likelihood 기반 benchmark에서 여전히 경쟁력이 있으며, validation perplexity는 더 나쁘지만 GSM8K에서는 autoregressive 및 masked diffusion model을 능가함을 보인다. 전반적으로, <strong>우리의 결과는 masked diffusion이 diffusion language modeling의 미래라는 관점과 perplexity만으로 cross-algorithm comparison이 충분하다는 관점을 모두 चुनौती한다</strong>.</p>"},{"id":"60790","en":"RE-TRAC: REcursive TRAjectory Compression for Deep Search Agents","ko":"RE-TRAC: Deep Search Agent를 위한 REcursive TRAjectory Compression","authors":"jialiang zhu, Gongrui Zhang, Xiaolong Ma, Lin Xu, Miaosen Zhang, Ruiqi Yang, Song Wang, Kai Qiu, Zhirong Wu, Qi Dai, Ruichun Ma, Bei Liu, Yifan Yang, Chong Luo, Zhengyuan Yang, Linjie Li, Lijuan Wang, Weizhu Chen, Xin Geng, Baining Guo","pos":"#1806","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=wjNTbZKIvC","abs":"<p>LLM-based deep research agents are largely built on the ReAct framework. This linear design makes it difficult to revisit earlier states, branch into alternative search directions, or maintain global awareness under long contexts, often leading to local optima, redundant exploration, and inefficient search.  We propose Re-TRAC, an agentic framework that performs cross-trajectory exploration by generating a structured state representation after each trajectory to summarize evidence, uncertainties, failures, and future plans, and conditioning subsequent trajectories on this state representation. This enables iterative reflection and globally informed planning, reframing research as a progressive process. Empirical results show that Re-TRAC consistently outperforms ReAct by 15–20% on BrowseComp with frontier LLMs. For smaller models, we introduce Re-TRAC-aware supervised fine-tuning, achieving state-of-the-art performance at comparable scales. Notably, Re-TRAC shows a monotonic reduction in tool calls and token usage across rounds, indicating progressively targeted exploration driven by cross-trajectory reflection rather than redundant search.</p>","absKo":"<p>LLM 기반 deep research agent는 대체로 ReAct framework 위에서 구축된다. 이 선형적 설계는 이전 state를 다시 살펴보거나, 대안적인 search 방향으로 분기하거나, 긴 context에서 global awareness를 유지하기 어렵게 만들어, 종종 local optimum, 중복 탐색, 비효율적인 search로 이어진다. 우리는 Re-TRAC를 제안하는데, 이는 각 trajectory 이후 evidence, uncertainty, failure, future plan을 요약하는 structured state representation을 생성하고 이후 trajectory를 이 state representation에 조건화하여 cross-trajectory exploration을 수행하는 agentic framework이다. 이를 통해 iterative reflection과 globally informed planning이 가능해지며, research를 점진적인 process로 재구성한다. 실험 결과, Re-TRAC는 frontier LLM에서 BrowseComp에 대해 ReAct를 일관되게 15–20% 상회한다. 더 작은 model의 경우, 우리는 Re-TRAC-aware supervised fine-tuning을 도입하여 비슷한 scale에서 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성한다. 특히 Re-TRAC는 round가 진행될수록 tool call과 token usage가 단조롭게 감소하는데, 이는 중복 검색이 아니라 cross-trajectory reflection에 의해 점점 더 목표화된 탐색이 이루어짐을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"65461","en":"RLVE: Scaling Up Reinforcement Learning for Language Models with Adaptive Verifiable Environments","ko":"RLVE: 적응형 검증 가능 환경으로 언어 모델을 위한 강화학습 확장","authors":"Zhiyuan Zeng, Hamish Ivison, Yiping Wang, Lifan Yuan, Stella Li, Zhuorui Ye, Siting Li, Jacqueline He, Runlong Zhou, Tong Chen, Chenyang Zhao, Yulia Tsvetkov, Simon Du, Natasha Jaques, Hao Peng, Pang Wei Koh, Hannaneh Hajishirzi","pos":"#1809","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=DRqjMnDQGq","abs":"<p>We introduce Reinforcement Learning (RL) with Adaptive Verifiable Environments (RLVE), an approach using verifiable environments that procedurally generate problems and provide algorithmically verifiable rewards, to scale up RL for language models (LMs). RLVE enables each verifiable environment to dynamically adapt its problem difficulty distribution to the policy model's capabilities as training progresses. In contrast, static data distributions often lead to vanishing learning signals when problems are either too easy or too hard for the policy. To implement RLVE, we create RLVE-Gym, a large-scale suite of 400 verifiable environments carefully developed through manual environment engineering. Using RLVE-Gym, we show that environment scaling, i.e., expanding the collection of training environments, consistently improves generalizable reasoning capabilities. RLVE with joint training across all 400 environments in RLVE-Gym yields a 3.37% absolute average improvement across six reasoning benchmarks, starting from one of the strongest 1.5B reasoning LMs. By comparison, continuing this LM's original RL training yields only a 0.49% average absolute gain despite using over 3x more compute. We will release our code publicly.</p>"},{"id":"64206","en":"RSPO: Regularized Self-Play Alignment of Large Language Models","ko":"RSPO: 대형 언어 모델의 정규화된 셀프 플레이 정렬","authors":"Xiaohang Tang, Sangwoong Yoon, Seongho Son, Huizhuo Yuan, Quanquan Gu, Ilija Bogunovic","pos":"#1810","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=PysPgClt8e","abs":"Self-play-based policy optimization has emerged as an effective approach for fine-tuning large language models (LLMs), formulating preference optimization as a two-player game. However, the regularization with respect to the reference policy, which is crucial for mitigating over-optimization, has been insufficiently investigated in self-play alignment. To study the impact of different regularization strategies, we propose \\textbf{Regularized Self-Play Policy Optimization (RSPO)}, a novel framework that unifies prior methods and enables simple plug-and-play regularizers, meanwhile preserving convergence to Nash equilibrium of the corresponding regularized game.  We empirically show that RSPO with appropriate regularizers can substantially improve the length-controlled win rate (LCWR) on AlpacaEval-2 across a range of base models, while also achieving consistently superior performance on Arena-Hard, MT-Bench, ArmoRM, and response diversity. In particular, RSPO improves unregularized self-play baseline (SPPO) on AlpacaEval-2 LCWR from $28.5\\%$ to $ 35.4\\%$ with base model Mistral-7B, from $38.77\\%$ to $43.66\\%$ with LLaMA-8B, and from $50.54\\%$ to $51.83\\%$ with Gemma-2B. Combining simplicity, convergence guarantees, and significant empirical gains, RSPO offers a strong foundation for exploring regularized self-play in alignment.","absKo":"자기대국(self-play) 기반 policy optimization은 preference optimization을 두 플레이어 게임으로 정식화하여 large language model (LLM)을 fine-tuning하는 효과적인 접근으로 부상했다. 그러나 과도한 최적화를 완화하는 데 중요한 reference policy에 대한 regularization은 self-play alignment에서 충분히 연구되지 않았다. 서로 다른 regularization strategy의 영향을 연구하기 위해, 우리는 기존 방법들을 통합하고 간단한 plug-and-play regularizer를 가능하게 하면서, 대응하는 regularized game의 Nash equilibrium으로의 수렴을 보존하는 새로운 framework인 \\textbf{Regularized Self-Play Policy Optimization (RSPO)}를 제안한다. 우리는 적절한 regularizer를 사용한 RSPO가 다양한 base model에서 AlpacaEval-2의 length-controlled win rate (LCWR)를 상당히 개선하고, Arena-Hard, MT-Bench, ArmoRM, response diversity에서도 일관되게 더 우수한 성능을 달성함을 경험적으로 보인다. 특히 RSPO는 Mistral-7B base model에서 AlpacaEval-2 LCWR를 비정규화 self-play baseline (SPPO)의 $28.5\\%$에서 $35.4\\%$로, LLaMA-8B에서는 $38.77\\%$에서 $43.66\\%$로, Gemma-2B에서는 $50.54\\%$에서 $51.83\\%$로 향상시킨다. 단순함, 수렴 보장, 그리고 큰 실증적 향상을 결합한 RSPO는 alignment에서 regularized self-play를 탐구하기 위한 강력한 기반을 제공한다."},{"id":"62531","en":"PS-PPO : Prefix-Sampling PPO for Critic-Free RLHF","ko":"PS-PPO: critic-free RLHF를 위한 Prefix-Sampling PPO","authors":"Doo Hwan Hwang, Kee-Eung Kim","pos":"#1902","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=flDa73nyVx","abs":"<p>Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback (RLHF) for Large Language Models increasingly relies on critic-free methods as a practical alternative to actor–critic training. Despite their simplicity, existing critic-free approaches propagate a trajectory-level learning signal uniformly across all tokens appearing in the trajectory. This requires full-trajectory update for every rollouts, leading to substantial optimization cost for long reasoning traces although the feedback signal is effectively determined early in the trajectory. We propose Prefix-Sampling Proximal Policy Optimization (PS-PPO), a compute-efficient critic-free method for RLHF that exploits this temporal redundancy. PS-PPO introduces a prompt-conditioned cutoff distribution and samples a cutoff timestep for each trajectory. Policy gradient updates are then applied only up to the sampled cutoff timestep, while a correction mechanism ensures that the resulting truncated gradient estimator remains unbiased with respect to the full-trajectory objective. This procedure bypasses later tokens whose contribution to the feedback signal is negligible, without distorting the underlying learning signal. Experiments on mathematical reasoning and RLHF benchmarks show that PS-PPO achieves large reductions in training compute and peak GPU memory, while maintaining accuracy comparable to strong critic-free baselines.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large Language Model을 위한 Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback(RLHF)은 actor-critic training의 실용적 대안으로 critic-free method에 점점 더 의존하고 있다. 단순함에도 불구하고, 기존 critic-free 접근법은 trajectory 전체에서 발생한 모든 token에 trajectory-level learning signal을 균일하게 전파한다. 이는 모든 rollout마다 전체 trajectory update를 요구하므로, feedback signal이 실제로는 trajectory 초반에 이미 결정되는 경우에도 긴 reasoning trace에 대해 상당한 optimization cost를 초래한다. 우리는 이러한 temporal redundancy를 활용하는 compute-efficient critic-free RLHF 방법인 Prefix-Sampling Proximal Policy Optimization(PS-PPO)을 제안한다. PS-PPO는 prompt-conditioned cutoff distribution을 도입하고, 각 trajectory마다 cutoff timestep을 샘플링한다. 그런 다음 policy gradient update는 샘플링된 cutoff timestep까지에만 적용되며, correction mechanism이 truncated gradient estimator가 full-trajectory objective에 대해 여전히 unbiased하도록 보장한다. 이 절차는 feedback signal에 대한 기여가 미미한 이후 token들을 왜곡 없이 건너뛴다. 수학적 추론과 RLHF benchmark에 대한 실험은 PS-PPO가 강력한 critic-free baseline과 비슷한 정확도를 유지하면서 training compute와 peak GPU memory를 크게 줄임을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"66045","en":"PADA-Coder: Improving Plan-Following Code Generation via Perturbation-Verified Attention Distillation and Dynamic Alignment","ko":"PADA-Coder: 섭동 검증 Attention 증류와 동적 정렬을 통한 계획 준수 코드 생성 향상","authors":"Yihong Huang, KE QIN, Rongzheng Wang, Muquan Li, Jiakai Li, Xiurui Xie, Shuang Liang","pos":"#1903","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=7ZicVirxBC","abs":"<p>The Plan-then-Code paradigm effectively enhances Large Language Models (LLMs) in complex code generation by decomposing reasoning into explicit, interpretable steps. However, introducing the plan and verification report substantially enlarges the context, which in turn misdirects the model’s attention toward irrelevant tokens and the most recently generated code. This effect leads the model to overlook critical constraints and to generate incorrect code, especially for small-scale LLMs (less than 8B). To address this issue, we propose \\textbf{P}erturbation-Verified \\textbf{A}ttention \\textbf{D}istillation and Dynamic \\textbf{A}lignment (PADA).  PADA identifies the key tokens most critical to the student model and constructs the optimal attention target matrix, dynamically aligning the student’s focus with key tokens for each plan step. We evaluate PADA with two teacher models and three student models across seven benchmarks, and the results show that PADA improves Pass@1 by up to 16.7\\% and outperforms SOTA methods in all settings. Our code is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/PADA-coder</p>"},{"id":"60715","en":"Normalized Rewards for Preference Optimization","ko":"Preference Optimization을 위한 정규화 보상","authors":"Shawn Im, Federico Danieli, Skyler Seto, Barry-John Theobald, Katherine Metcalf","pos":"#1907","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=xFbdOV2Ma7","abs":"<p>Direct Alignment Algorithms (DAAs) such as DPO have become a common way to post-train and align LLMs with human preferences. However, DAAs have been observed to over-optimize their implicit reward model and decrease the likelihood of preferred responses. This results in a decrease in the total likelihood assigned to responses seen in the preference dataset, potentially resulting in undesirable behavior. To counteract this undesired side-effect of DAAs, we examine the effect of using objectives that add a regularization term to maintain the total length-normalized probabilities of the chosen and rejected responses. To better understand over-optimization, we investigate how response likelihood changes are distributed over the tokens with and without regularization. We find that a significant portion of the likelihood changes are due to a small set of outlier tokens, which explains how DAAs improve generation quality despite decreasing the likelihoods of chosen responses. We apply the proposed regularization to reference-based (DPO) and reference-free (SimPO) methods and find (1) improved trade-offs between generation quality and general benchmark capability and (2) improvements in reward modeling across datasets. For example, on Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct, we see both a &gt;20\\% relative increase in AlpacaEval2 scores and &gt;9\\% relative performance gains on general benchmarks. Additionally, we find that the added regularization term effectively mitigates the amount of displacement within preferred responses overall, and for the outlier tokens specifically, by utilizing low-likelihood tokens.</p>","absKo":"<p>DPO와 같은 Direct Alignment Algorithms(DAAs)는 LLM을 인간 선호에 맞게 post-train하고 align하는 일반적인 방법이 되었다. 그러나 DAAs는 암묵적인 reward model을 과도하게 최적화하여 선호되는 응답의 likelihood를 낮추는 현상이 관찰되었다. 그 결과 preference dataset에서 본 응답들에 할당되는 total likelihood가 감소하며, 이는 바람직하지 않은 행동으로 이어질 수 있다. 이러한 DAAs의 원치 않는 부작용에 대응하기 위해, 우리는 선택된 응답과 거부된 응답의 total length-normalized probabilities를 유지하도록 regularization term을 추가하는 objectives의 효과를 검토한다. over-optimization을 더 잘 이해하기 위해, regularization 유무에 따라 response likelihood 변화가 token들에 걸쳐 어떻게 분포하는지 조사했다. 그 결과 likelihood 변화의 상당 부분이 소수의 outlier token들로 인해 발생하며, 이것이 선택된 응답의 likelihood가 감소하더라도 DAAs가 generation quality를 개선하는 이유를 설명한다는 점을 확인했다. 우리는 제안한 regularization을 reference-based(DPO) 및 reference-free(SimPO) 방법에 적용했고, (1) generation quality와 general benchmark capability 사이의 trade-off 개선, (2) datasets 전반의 reward modeling 개선을 확인했다. 예를 들어 Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct에서 AlpacaEval2 score는 20%를 넘는 상대적 향상을 보였고, general benchmark에서는 9%를 넘는 상대적 성능 향상을 보였다. 또한 추가된 regularization term은 low-likelihood token을 활용함으로써 preferred response 전반, 특히 outlier token들에 대한 displacement를 효과적으로 완화함을 확인했다.</p>"},{"id":"61089","en":"Multilingual Safety Alignment Via Sparse Weight Editing","ko":"Sparse Weight Editing을 통한 다국어 안전성 정렬","authors":"Jiaming Liang, Zhaoxin Wang, Handing Wang","pos":"#1908","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=tlPhEl24fM","abs":"<p>Large Language Models (LLMs) exhibit significant safety disparities across languages, with low-resource languages (LRLs) often bypassing safety guardrails established for high-resource languages (HRLs) like English. Existing solutions, such as multilingual supervised fine-tuning (SFT) or Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback (RLHF), are computationally expensive and de- pendent on scarce multilingual safety data. In this paper, we propose a novel, training-free alignment framework based on Sparse Weight Editing. Identifying that safety capabilities are localized within a sparse set of ”safety neurons,” we formulate the cross-lingual alignment problem as a constrained linear transformation. We derive a closed-form solution to optimally map the harmful representations of LRLs to the robust safety subspaces of HRLs, while preserving general utility via a null-space projection constraint. Extensive experiments across 8 languages and multiple model families (Llama-3, Qwen-2.5) demonstrate that our method significantly reduces Attack Success Rate (ASR) in LRLs with negligible impact on general reasoning capabilities, all achieved with a single, data-efficient calculation.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large Language Models(LLMs)은 언어 간에 상당한 safety disparity를 보이며, low-resource language(LRLs)는 종종 English와 같은 high-resource language(HRLs)에 대해 구축된 safety guardrail을 우회한다. multilingual supervised fine-tuning(SFT)이나 Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback(RLHF)과 같은 기존 해결책은 계산 비용이 많이 들고 희소한 multilingual safety data에 의존한다. 본 논문에서는 Sparse Weight Editing 기반의 새로운 training-free alignment framework를 제안한다. 안전성 능력이 희소한 집합의 “safety neuron”에 국소화되어 있음을 식별하고, cross-lingual alignment 문제를 constrained linear transformation으로 정식화한다. 우리는 일반적인 utility를 null-space projection constraint로 보존하면서, LRL의 harmful representation을 HRL의 견고한 safety subspace에 최적으로 매핑하는 closed-form solution을 도출한다. 8개 언어와 여러 model family(Llama-3, Qwen-2.5)에 걸친 광범위한 실험은, 우리의 방법이 general reasoning capability에 거의 영향을 주지 않으면서 LRL의 Attack Success Rate(ASR)을 유의미하게 감소시키며, 이를 단일의 data-efficient calculation만으로 달성함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"63848","en":"Mitigating Conversational Inertia in Multi-Turn Agents","ko":"멀티턴 에이전트의 대화 관성 완화","authors":"Yang Wan, Zheng Cao, Zhenhao Zhang, Zhengwen Zeng, Shuheng Shen, Changhua Meng, Linchao Zhu","pos":"#1911","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=TCWXiFT7gj","abs":"<p>Large language models excel as few-shot learners when provided with appropriate demonstrations, yet this strength becomes problematic in multi-turn agent scenarios, where LLMs erroneously mimic their own previous responses as few-shot examples. Through attention analysis, we identify \\textbf{conversational inertia}, a phenomenon where models exhibit strong diagonal attention to previous responses, which is associated with imitation bias that constrains exploration. This reveals a tension when transforming few-shot LLMs into agents: longer context enriches environmental feedback for exploitation, yet also amplifies conversational inertia that undermines exploration. Our key insight is that for identical states, actions generated with longer contexts exhibit stronger inertia than those with shorter contexts, enabling construction of preference pairs without environment rewards. Based on this, we propose Context Preference Learning to calibrate model preferences to favor low-inertia responses over high-inertia ones. We further provide context management strategies at inference time to balance exploration and exploitation. Experimental results across eight agentic environments and one deep research scenario validate that our framework reduces conversational inertia and achieves performance improvements.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large language model은 적절한 demonstration이 주어질 때 few-shot learner로서 뛰어나지만, 이 강점은 multi-turn agent 시나리오에서는 문제가 된다. LLM이 자신의 이전 응답을 few-shot example처럼 잘못 모방하기 때문이다. attention 분석을 통해 우리는 \\textbf{conversational inertia}를 식별한다. 이는 model이 이전 응답에 대해 강한 diagonal attention을 보이는 현상으로, 탐색을 제약하는 imitation bias와 관련된다. 이는 few-shot LLM을 agent로 전환할 때의 긴장을 드러낸다. 더 긴 context는 exploit을 위한 환경 피드백을 풍부하게 하지만, 동시에 탐색을 저해하는 conversational inertia를 증폭시킨다. 우리의 핵심 통찰은 동일한 state에 대해, 더 긴 context로 생성된 action이 더 짧은 context로 생성된 action보다 더 강한 inertia를 보인다는 점이며, 이를 통해 environment reward 없이 preference pair를 구성할 수 있다는 것이다. 이를 바탕으로 우리는 모델 preference를 보정하여 high-inertia response보다 low-inertia response를 선호하도록 만드는 Context Preference Learning을 제안한다. 또한 inference 시점에서 exploration과 exploitation의 균형을 맞추기 위한 context management 전략도 제시한다. 여덟 개의 agentic environment와 하나의 deep research scenario에 대한 실험 결과는 우리의 framework가 conversational inertia를 줄이고 성능 향상을 달성함을 검증한다.</p>"},{"id":"60515","en":"Memora: A Harmonic Memory Representation Balancing Abstraction and Specificity","ko":"Memora: 추상성과 구체성의 균형을 맞추는 Harmonic Memory Representation","authors":"Menglin Xia, Xuchao Zhang, Shantanu Dixit, Paramaguru Harimurugan, Rujia Wang, Victor Ruehle, Robert A Sim, Chetan Bansal, Saravanakumar Rajmohan","pos":"#1913","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=zSrvkj0ers","abs":"<p>Agent memory systems must accommodate continuously growing information while supporting efficient, context-aware retrieval for downstream tasks. Abstraction is essential for scaling agent memory, yet it often comes at the cost of specificity, obscuring the fine-grained details required for effective reasoning. We introduce Memora, a harmonic memory representation that structurally balances abstraction and specificity. Memora organizes information via its <em>primary abstractions</em> that index concrete memory values and consolidate related updates into unified memory entries, while <em>cue anchors</em> expand retrieval access across diverse aspects of the memory and connect related memories. Building on this structure, we employ a retrieval policy that actively exploits these memory connections to retrieve relevant information beyond direct semantic similarity. Theoretically, we show that standard Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) and Knowledge Graph (KG)-based memory systems emerge as special cases of our framework. Empirically, Memora establishes a new state-of-the-art on the LoCoMo and LongMemEval benchmarks, demonstrating better retrieval relevance and reasoning effectiveness as memory scales.</p>","absKo":"<p>agent memory system은 downstream task를 위한 효율적이고 context-aware한 retrieval을 지원하면서 지속적으로 증가하는 정보를 수용해야 한다. abstraction은 agent memory를 확장하는 데 필수적이지만, 종종 specificity를 희생하여 효과적인 추론에 필요한 세밀한 세부 정보를 가려 버린다. 우리는 abstraction과 specificity 사이를 구조적으로 균형 있게 맞춘 harmonic memory representation인 Memora를 제안한다. Memora는 구체적인 memory value를 인덱싱하고 관련 update를 통합된 memory entry로 합치는 <em>primary abstractions</em>와, memory의 다양한 측면 전반으로 retrieval 접근을 확장하고 관련 memory를 연결하는 <em>cue anchors</em>를 통해 정보를 조직한다. 이 구조를 바탕으로, 우리는 직접적인 semantic similarity를 넘어 관련 정보를 retrieval하기 위해 이러한 memory connection을 적극적으로 활용하는 retrieval policy를 사용한다. 이론적으로 우리는 표준 Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)과 Knowledge Graph (KG) 기반 memory system이 우리의 프레임워크의 특수한 경우로 나타남을 보인다. 실증적으로 Memora는 LoCoMo와 LongMemEval benchmark에서 새로운 state-of-the-art를 수립하며, memory가 확장될수록 더 나은 retrieval relevance와 추론 효과를 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"65040","en":"Geometry-Aware Decoding with Wasserstein-Regularized Truncation and Mass Penalties for Large Language Models","ko":"대규모 언어 모델을 위한 Wasserstein-Regularized Truncation 및 Mass Penalty를 활용한 Geometry-Aware Decoding","authors":"Arash Gholamidavoodi, Navid Rezazadeh, Seyed Davoudi, Pouya Pezeshkpour","pos":"#2004","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=HSuU4xBmAv","abs":"<p>Large language models (LLMs) must balance diversity and creativity against logical coherence in open-ended generation. Existing truncation-based samplers are effective but largely heuristic, relying mainly on probability mass and entropy while ignoring semantic geometry of the token space. We present Top-W , a geometry-aware truncation rule that uses Wasserstein distance—defined over token-embedding geometry—to keep the cropped distribution close to the original, while explicitly balancing retained probability mass against the entropy of the kept set. Our theory yields a simple closed-form structure for the fixed-potential subset update: depending on the mass–entropy trade-off, the optimal crop either collapses to a single token or takes the form of a one-dimensional prefix that can be found efficiently with a linear scan. We implement Top-W using efficient geometry-based potentials (nearest-set or k-NN) and pair it with an alternating decoding routine that keeps the standard truncation-and-sampling interface unchanged. Extensive experiments on four benchmarks (GSM8K, GPQA, AlpacaEval, and MT-Bench) across three instruction-tuned models show that Top-W consistently outperforms prior state-of-the-art decoding approaches achieving up to 33.7% improvement. Moreover, we find that Top-W not only improves accuracy-focused performance, but also boosts creativity under judge-based open-ended evaluation. We will release all code upon acceptance.</p>"},{"id":"65952","en":"Judgment Operators: A Composition-Invariant Substrate for Multi-Agent Action Spaces","ko":"Judgment Operator: 멀티에이전트 행동 공간을 위한 합성 불변 기반","authors":"Jun Li","pos":"#2009","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=8Ysr6x0XMv","abs":"As large language models (LLMs) are increasingly composed into heterogeneous multi-agent systems, a fundamental reliability challenge emerges: knowledge and governance **fragment across agents**, leading to composition-dependent behaviors and **linear scaling** of violations. We introduce **Judgment Operators (JO)**, a decision-time framework that adapts corrective projection via precedent memory from agent actions onto admissible sets. JO establishes a *unified projection interface* in which governance constraints $\\mathcal{C}$ define the *target admissible set* and corrective precedents $\\mathcal{P}$ provide *executable corrective knowledge* for adapting the projection map. The centralized operator $\\Pi_J: \\mathcal{X} \\to \\mathcal{X}_J$ implements four-way intervention semantics (*Allow*, *Edit*, *Escalate*, *Deny*), enabling minimal repair without modifying agent internals.  We formalize JO as an *adaptive projection operator* and establish guarantees of: (1) **composition-invariant enforcement** with **constant violation probability** (vs. linear scaling without JO); (2) **sublinear mistake accumulation** for online adaptation via JO-A under recurring violations; and (3) **semantic preservation** for code transformation tasks via structure-preserving projection. Empirically, JO provides *portable corrective knowledge transfer*: (1) **capability**---learns and reuses corrective precedents under recurring violations, improving task success over strong baselines; (2) **governance**---achieves *near-perfect constraint enforcement* in fully verifiable settings (0\\% observed violation rate vs. 48--68\\% for baseline methods); and (3) **portability**---enables *13.5--20.5\\% absolute zero-shot cross-model transfer* where few-shot prompting fails. Judgment Operators thus provide a **portable, auditable, and composable interface** for both decision-time governance and capability injection in multi-agent LLM systems, addressing fragmentation at its architectural root through **adaptive, composition-invariant projection**."},{"id":"61766","en":"Early Decisions Matter: Proximity Bias and Initial Trajectory Shaping in Non-Autoregressive Diffusion Language Models","ko":"초기 결정의 중요성: Non-Autoregressive Diffusion Language Model의 근접성 Bias와 초기 Trajectory 형성","authors":"Jiyeon Kim, Sungik Choi, Yongrae Jo, Moontae Lee, Minjoon Seo","pos":"#2104","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=n90nG9NXBF","abs":"<p>Diffusion-based language models(dLLMs) have emerged as a promising alternative to autoregressive language models, offering the potential for parallel token generation and bidirectional context modeling. However, harnessing this flexibility for fully non-autoregressive decoding remains an open question, particularly for reasoning and planning tasks. In this work, we investigate non-autoregressive decoding in dLLMs by systematically analyzing its inference dynamics along the temporal axis. Specifically, we uncover an inherent failure modes in confidence-based non-autoregressive generation stem from a strong proximity bias—the denoising order tends to concentrate on spatially adjacent tokens. This local dependency leads to spatial error propagation, rendering the entire trajectory critically contingent on the initial unmasking position. Leveraging this insight, we present a minimal-intervention approach that guides early token selection, employing a lightweight planner and end-of-sequence temperature annealing. We thoroughly evaluate our method on various reasoning and planning tasks and observe substantial overall improvement over existing heuristic baselines without significant computational overhead.</p>","absKo":"<p>Diffusion-based language models(dLLMs)는 autoregressive language models의 유망한 대안으로 부상했으며, 병렬 token generation과 bidirectional context modeling의 가능성을 제공한다. 그러나 이러한 유연성을 fully non-autoregressive decoding에 활용하는 문제는 여전히 열려 있으며, 특히 reasoning과 planning tasks에서 그렇다. 본 연구에서는 시간 축에 따른 inference dynamics를 체계적으로 분석하여 dLLMs의 non-autoregressive decoding을 조사한다. 구체적으로, confidence-based non-autoregressive generation의 고유한 failure mode가 강한 proximity bias에서 비롯됨을 밝혀낸다. 즉, denoising order가 공간적으로 인접한 토큰들에 집중되는 경향이 있다. 이러한 local dependency는 spatial error propagation을 초래하여, 전체 trajectory가 초기 unmasking position에 결정적으로 좌우되게 만든다. 이 통찰을 바탕으로, early token selection을 유도하는 minimal-intervention 접근법을 제시하며, lightweight planner와 end-of-sequence temperature annealing을 사용한다. 우리는 다양한 reasoning 및 planning tasks에서 이 방법을 철저히 평가했으며, 상당한 computational overhead 없이 기존 heuristic baselines 대비 전반적인 성능 향상을 확인했다.</p>"},{"id":"63478","en":"DOT-MoE: Differentiable Optimal Transport for MoEfication","ko":"DOT-MoE: MoE화를 위한 미분 가능 최적 수송","authors":"Udbhav Bamba, Arnav Chavan, Aryamaan Thakur, Deepak Gupta, Steven Teig","pos":"#2109","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=WrXyXq11Yc","abs":"<p>The scaling of Large Language Models (LLMs) has driven significant performance gains but created substantial challenges in inference efficiency. While Mixture of Experts (MoEs) architectures address this by decoupling model size from inference cost, training MoEs from scratch is often unstable and compute intensive. Conversion of pre-trained dense models into sparse MoEs has emerged as an alternative solution; however, existing methods typically rely on heuristic neuron clustering or random splitting to partition Feed-Forward Networks (FFNs) into experts. In this work, we propose DOT-MoE, a novel framework that formulates the decomposition of dense layers as a Differentiable Optimal Transport (DOT) problem. Instead of static heuristics, we model neuron assignment as a balanced transport problem, utilizing differentiable Sinkhorn-Knopp iterations to enforce strict expert capacity constraints. Furthermore, we utilize Straight-Through Estimators (STE) to jointly learn the discrete neuron-to-expert assignment and the token-to-expert routing policy end-to-end. Extensive experiments across multiple architectures and benchmarks demonstrate that DOT-MoE significantly outperforms structured pruning, heuristic clustering, and random-split baselines, retaining 90% of the original dense model's performance while reducing active parameters by 50%.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large Language Models (LLMs)의 scaling은 성능을 크게 향상시켰지만 inference efficiency 측면에서 상당한 도전을 초래했다. Mixture of Experts (MoEs) architecture는 model size와 inference cost를 분리함으로써 이를 해결하지만, MoE를 처음부터 학습하는 것은 종종 불안정하고 계산 비용이 크다. 사전 학습된 dense model을 sparse MoE로 변환하는 방식이 대안으로 떠올랐지만, 기존 방법들은 보통 heuristic neuron clustering이나 random splitting에 의존하여 Feed-Forward Networks (FFNs)를 expert로 분할한다. 본 연구에서는 dense layer의 분해를 Differentiable Optimal Transport (DOT) 문제로 정식화하는 새로운 framework인 DOT-MoE를 제안한다. 정적 heuristic 대신, 우리는 neuron assignment를 balanced transport problem으로 모델링하고, differentiable Sinkhorn-Knopp iteration을 사용하여 엄격한 expert capacity constraint를 강제한다. 더 나아가, Straight-Through Estimators (STE)를 활용하여 discrete neuron-to-expert assignment와 token-to-expert routing policy를 end-to-end로 공동 학습한다. 여러 architecture와 benchmark에 걸친 광범위한 실험은 DOT-MoE가 structured pruning, heuristic clustering, random-split baseline을 크게 능가하며, 활성 parameter를 50% 줄이면서도 원래 dense model 성능의 90%를 유지함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"62745","en":"DECOR: Learning to Decompose and Collaborate in Deep Search via Multi-Agent Reinforcement Learning","ko":"DECOR: Multi-Agent Reinforcement Learning을 통한 Deep Search의 분해와 협업 학습","authors":"Ruiqing Chen, Zekun Zhang, Gongduo Zhang, Lihong Gu, Lin Zhou","pos":"#2110","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=dkRAVqr347","abs":"Monolithic agents in deep search often suffer from \"cognitive overload,\" while existing multi-agent approaches mostly rely on frozen models that cannot learn from collaboration failures. To bridge this gap, we propose $\\textbf{DECOR}$ ($\\textbf{DE}$compose and $\\textbf{CO}$llaborate via $\\textbf{R}$ole-specialized agents),  a framework formulating deep search as a Multi-Agent Reinforcement Learning (MARL) problem. DECOR functionally decomposes the task into three specialized roles: a $\\textit{Planner}$ to navigate, a $\\textit{Filter}$ to curate a noise-reduced memory, and an $\\textit{Answerer}$ for synthesis. Unlike training-free orchestration, we jointly optimize these agents using a hybrid reward strategy that harmonizes role-specific intrinsic feedback with team-level outcome signals. Experiments on seven benchmarks show that DECOR significantly outperforms strong monolithic baselines, demonstrating the necessity of learning-based functional decomposition in handling cognitive overload.","absKo":"딥 서치에서 monolithic agent는 종종 \"cognitive overload\"를 겪는 반면, 기존 multi-agent 접근은 대부분 협업 실패로부터 학습할 수 없는 frozen model에 의존한다. 이러한 간극을 메우기 위해, 우리는 딥 서치를 Multi-Agent Reinforcement Learning (MARL) 문제로 공식화하는 framework인 $\\textbf{DECOR}$ ($\\textbf{DE}$compose and $\\textbf{CO}$llaborate via $\\textbf{R}$ole-specialized agents)를 제안한다. DECOR는 task를 세 가지 specialized role로 기능적으로 분해한다: 탐색을 담당하는 $\\textit{Planner}$, noise를 줄인 memory를 선별하는 $\\textit{Filter}$, 그리고 종합을 수행하는 $\\textit{Answerer}$이다. training-free orchestration과 달리, 우리는 role-specific intrinsic feedback와 team-level outcome signal을 조화시키는 hybrid reward strategy를 사용하여 이 agent들을 공동 최적화한다. 7개 benchmark에서의 실험은 DECOR가 강력한 monolithic baseline을 크게 능가함을 보여주며, cognitive overload를 다루는 데 있어 learning-based functional decomposition의 필요성을 입증한다."},{"id":"60796","en":"Contextual Rollout Bandits for Reinforcement Learning with Verifiable Rewards","ko":"검증 가능한 보상을 갖는 Reinforcement Learning을 위한 Contextual Rollout Bandit","authors":"Xiaodong Lu, Xiaohan Wang, Jiajun Chai, Guojun Yin, Wei Lin, Zhijun Chen, Yu Luo, Fuzhen Zhuang, Yikun Ban, deqing wang","pos":"#2112","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=weMYE1B16x","abs":"<p>Reinforcement Learning with Verifiable Rewards (RLVR) is an effective paradigm for improving the reasoning capabilities of large language models. However, existing RLVR methods utilize rollouts in an indiscriminate and short-horizon manner: responses of heterogeneous quality within each prompt are treated uniformly, and historical rollouts are discarded after a single use. This leads to noisy supervision, poor sample efficiency, and suboptimal policy updates. We address these issues by formulating rollout scheduling in RLVR as a contextual bandit problem and proposing a unified neural scheduling framework that adaptively selects high-value rollouts throughout training. Each rollout is treated as an arm whose reward is defined by the induced performance gain between consecutive optimization steps. The resulting scheduler supports both noise-aware intra-group selection and adaptive global reuse of historical rollouts within a single principled framework. We provide theoretical justification by deriving sublinear regret bounds and showing that enlarging the rollout buffer improves the achievable performance upper bound. Experiments on six mathematical reasoning benchmarks demonstrate consistent gains in performance and training efficiency across multiple RLVR optimization methods.</p>","absKo":"<p>Reinforcement Learning with Verifiable Rewards(RLVR)는 대규모 언어 모델의 추론 능력을 향상시키는 효과적인 패러다임이다. 그러나 기존 RLVR 방법은 rollout을 무차별적이고 짧은 horizon 방식으로 활용한다. 즉, 각 prompt 내에서 품질이 이질적인 response들을 동일하게 취급하고, 과거 rollout은 한 번 사용한 뒤 폐기한다. 이로 인해 supervision이 noisy해지고, sample efficiency가 낮아지며, policy update도 최적에 미치지 못한다. 우리는 rollout scheduling을 contextual bandit 문제로 정식화하고, 학습 전반에 걸쳐 높은 가치의 rollout을 적응적으로 선택하는 통합 neural scheduling framework를 제안함으로써 이러한 문제를 해결한다. 각 rollout은 arm으로 간주되며, 그 reward는 연속된 optimization step 사이에서 유도되는 performance gain으로 정의된다. 그 결과 얻어지는 scheduler는 noise-aware intra-group selection과 과거 rollout의 adaptive global reuse를 하나의 원칙적인 프레임워크 안에서 모두 지원한다. 우리는 sublinear regret bound를 유도하고 rollout buffer를 키우면 달성 가능한 performance upper bound가 향상됨을 보임으로써 이론적 타당성을 제시한다. 여섯 개의 수학 추론 benchmark에서의 실험은 여러 RLVR optimization 방법 전반에 걸쳐 성능과 학습 효율의 일관된 향상을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"63945","en":"On Group Relative Policy Optimization Collapse in Agent Search: The Lazy Likelihood-Displacement","ko":"에이전트 검색에서의 Group Relative Policy Optimization 붕괴에 대하여: lazy likelihood-displacement","authors":"wenlong deng, Yushu Li, Boying Gong, YI REN, Christos Thrampoulidis, Xiaoxiao Li","pos":"#216","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=SJ13vBxetN","abs":"<p>Tool-integrated (TI) reinforcement learning (RL) enables large language models (LLMs) to perform multi-step reasoning by interacting with external tools such as search engines and retrievers. Group Relative Policy Optimization (GRPO), exemplified by the recent Search-R1, offers fast convergence and a value-free formulation that makes it appealing for this setting, yet consistently suffers from training collapse. We identify Lazy Likelihood Displacement (LLD), a systematic reduction or stagnation in the likelihood of both correct and incorrect responses, as the core mechanism driving this failure. LLD emerges early and triggers a self-reinforcing LLD Death Spiral, where declining likelihood leads to low-confidence responses, inflating gradients, and ultimately causing collapse. We empirically characterize this process across models on a Search-R1-style, search-integrated question answering task, revealing a consistent three-phase trajectory: early stagnation, steady decay, and accelerated collapse. To address this, we propose a likelihood-preserving regularization LLDS that activates only when a response action’s likelihood decreases, and regularizes only the tokens responsible. This fine-grained structure mitigates LLD with minimal interference. Our method stabilizes training, prevents gradient explosion, and yields substantial performance improvements across seven benchmarks, including relative improvements of +45.2% on Qwen2.5-3B and +37.1% on Qwen2.5-7B over vanilla GRPO training. Our results establish LLD as a previously overlooked bottleneck in GRPO- based TIRL and provide a practical path toward stable, scalable training of tool-integrated RL.</p>","absKo":"<p>Tool-integrated (TI) reinforcement learning (RL)은 large language models (LLMs)가 search engine과 retriever 같은 외부 tool과 상호작용하면서 multi-step reasoning을 수행할 수 있게 한다. 최근 Search-R1로 대표되는 Group Relative Policy Optimization (GRPO)은 빠른 convergence와 value-free formulation 덕분에 이 설정에 매력적이지만, 학습 붕괴(training collapse)를 일관되게 겪는다. 우리는 이 실패를 유발하는 핵심 메커니즘으로, 정답 및 오답 응답 모두의 likelihood가 체계적으로 감소하거나 정체되는 Lazy Likelihood Displacement (LLD)를 식별한다. LLD는 초기에 나타나며, likelihood 하락이 low-confidence response를 유발하고, gradient를 증폭시키며, 결국 collapse로 이어지는 자기강화적 LLD Death Spiral을 촉발한다. 우리는 Search-R1 스타일의 search-integrated question answering task에서 여러 모델에 걸쳐 이 과정을 실증적으로 특성화하였고, early stagnation, steady decay, accelerated collapse라는 일관된 3단계 궤적을 확인했다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 응답 행동의 likelihood가 감소할 때에만 활성화되고, 그에 책임이 있는 token에만 regularization을 적용하는 likelihood-preserving regularization LLDS를 제안한다. 이러한 세밀한 구조는 최소한의 간섭으로 LLD를 완화한다. 우리의 방법은 학습을 안정화하고 gradient explosion을 방지하며, 7개 benchmark 전반에서 상당한 성능 향상을 보인다. 예를 들어 vanilla GRPO training 대비 Qwen2.5-3B에서 +45.2%, Qwen2.5-7B에서 +37.1%의 상대적 향상을 달성한다. 우리의 결과는 GRPO 기반 TIRL에서 이전에 간과되었던 병목으로 LLD를 확립하고, tool-integrated RL의 안정적이고 확장 가능한 학습으로 가는 실용적 경로를 제시한다.</p>"},{"id":"64306","en":"Agent World Model: Infinity Synthetic Environments for Agentic Reinforcement Learning","ko":"Agent World Model: 에이전트 강화학습을 위한 무한 합성 환경","authors":"Zhaoyang Wang, Boyi Liu, Yite Wang, Siwei Han, Zhewei Yao, Yuxiong He, Huaxiu Yao, Canwen Xu","pos":"#2202","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=OvLnVkV14P","abs":"<p>Recent advances in large language model (LLM) have empowered autonomous agents to perform complex tasks that require multi-turn interactions with external tools and environments. However, scaling such agent training is limited by the lack of diverse and reliable environments. In this paper, we propose Agent World Model (AWM), a fully synthetic environments generation pipeline. Using this pipeline, we scale to 1,000 environments covering everyday scenarios, in which agents can interact with rich toolsets (35 tools per environment on average) and obtain high-quality observations. Notably, these environments are code-driven and backed by databases, providing more reliable and consistent state transitions compared to environments simulated by LLMs. Moreover, they enable more efficient agent interaction compared to collecting trajectories from realistic environments. To demonstrate the effectiveness of this resource, we perform large-scale reinforcement learning for multi-turn tool-use agents. Thanks to the fully executable environments and accessible database states, we can also design reliable reward functions. Experiments on three benchmarks validate that training exclusively in synthetic environments, rather than benchmark-specific ones, yields strong out-of-distribution generalization.</p>","absKo":"<p>대규모 언어 모델(LLM)의 최근 발전은 autonomous agent가 외부 도구와 환경을 활용하는 다회차 상호작용이 필요한 복잡한 작업을 수행할 수 있게 했다. 그러나 이러한 agent 학습의 확장은 다양하고 신뢰할 수 있는 환경이 부족하다는 제약을 받는다. 본 논문에서는 완전히 synthetic한 환경 생성 파이프라인인 Agent World Model (AWM)을 제안한다. 이 파이프라인을 사용하여 우리는 일상적 시나리오를 포괄하는 1,000개의 환경으로 확장했으며, agent는 이 환경들에서 풍부한 toolset(환경당 평균 35개 도구)과 상호작용하고 고품질 관측을 획득할 수 있다. 특히 이러한 환경은 code-driven이며 database로 뒷받침되어, LLM이 시뮬레이션하는 환경보다 더 신뢰할 수 있고 일관된 state transition을 제공한다. 또한 현실적인 환경에서 trajectory를 수집하는 방식보다 더 효율적인 agent 상호작용을 가능하게 한다. 이 자원의 효과를 입증하기 위해, 우리는 다회차 tool-use agent에 대한 대규모 reinforcement learning을 수행한다. 완전히 executable한 환경과 접근 가능한 database state 덕분에, 우리는 신뢰할 수 있는 reward function도 설계할 수 있다. 세 개의 benchmark에서의 실험은 benchmark-specific 환경이 아니라 synthetic 환경에서만 학습해도 강력한 out-of-distribution generalization을 달성함을 검증한다.</p>"},{"id":"61969","en":"Chasing Moving Targets with Online Self-Play Reinforcement Learning for Safer Language Models","ko":"온라인 self-play 강화학습으로 이동 목표를 추적해 더 안전한 language model 달성","authors":"Mickel Liu, Liwei Jiang, Yancheng Liang, Simon Du, Yejin Choi, Tim Althoff, Natasha Jaques","pos":"#2212","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=l8PbMSZs2G","abs":"<p>Conventional large language model (LLM) safety alignment relies on a reactive, disjoint loop: attackers exploit a static model, then defenders patch exposed vulnerabilities. This sequential setup leads to attackers overfitting obsolete exploits while defenders perpetually lag behind emerging threats. To address this, we introduce Self-RedTeam, the first fully online self-play multi-agent reinforcement learning (MARL) algorithm that continuously co-evolves attacker and defender for robust safety alignment. A single policy self-plays as both attacker and defender, generating adversarial prompts and defending against them, with a reward model adjudicating outcomes. Each role uses hidden chain-of-thought for strategic planning. Grounded in two-player zero-sum game theory, we establish a theoretical safety guarantee: if the game converges to Nash Equilibrium, the defender produces safe responses against any adversarial input. Empirically, Self-RedTeam generalizes across five models from the Llama and Qwen families, uncovering more diverse attacks (+17.80% SBERT) and improving safety of RLHF-trained models by up to 95% across 14 benchmarks. Our work motivates a shift from reactive patching to proactive co-evolution, enabling LLM safety self-improvement via online self-play MARL.</p>","absKo":"<p>기존의 large language model(LLM) 안전 정렬은 반응적이고 분리된 루프에 의존한다. 공격자는 정적인 모델을 악용하고, 방어자는 노출된 취약점을 패치한다. 이러한 순차적 설정은 공격자가 이미 낡은 exploit에 과적합하고 방어자는 새롭게 등장하는 위협에 늘 뒤처지게 만든다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 Self-RedTeam을 제안한다. 이는 공격자와 방어자를 지속적으로 공진화시켜 강인한 안전 정렬을 달성하는 최초의 완전 온라인 self-play multi-agent reinforcement learning(MARL) 알고리즘이다. 하나의 policy가 공격자와 방어자 역할을 동시에 self-play하며 adversarial prompt를 생성하고 이를 방어하고, reward model이 결과를 판정한다. 각 역할은 전략적 계획을 위해 hidden chain-of-thought를 사용한다. 두 플레이어 zero-sum game theory에 기반하여, 우리는 이론적 안전 보장을 확립한다. 게임이 Nash equilibrium에 수렴하면, 방어자는 어떤 adversarial input에 대해서도 안전한 응답을 생성한다. 실험적으로 Self-RedTeam은 Llama와 Qwen 계열의 5개 모델에 걸쳐 일반화되며, 더 다양한 공격을 발견하고(+17.80% SBERT), 14개 benchmark 전반에서 RLHF로 학습된 모델의 안전성을 최대 95%까지 향상시킨다. 우리의 연구는 반응적 패치에서 능동적 공진화로의 전환을 촉진하며, online self-play MARL을 통한 LLM 안전성의 자기 개선을 가능하게 한다.</p>"},{"id":"61523","en":"Circle-RoPE: Cone-like Decoupled Rotary Positional Embedding for Vision-Language Models","ko":"Circle-RoPE: Vision-Language Models를 위한 Cone-like Decoupled Rotary Positional Embedding","authors":"Chengcheng Wang, Jianyuan Guo, Hongguang Li, Yuchuan Tian, Ying Nie, Chang Xu, Kai Han","pos":"#2213","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=pH7NRZx89n","abs":"Rotary Position Embedding (RoPE) is widely adopted in large language models, but when applied to vision-language models (VLMs) it couples text and image position indices and can introduce spurious cross-modal relative-position bias. We propose Per-Token Distance (PTD) to quantify cross-modal positional disentanglement, and we prove that $\\mathrm{PTD}=0$ is a sufficient condition to eliminate the geometric attention bias induced by RoPE. Guided by this criterion, we introduce Circle-RoPE, which remaps 2D image-token coordinates onto an annulus orthogonal to the text position axis, yielding a cone-like geometry where each text token is equidistant to all image tokens while preserving intra-image spatial structure. We further propose Alternating Geometry Encoding (AGE) to improve robustness by alternating RoPE variants across layers, and experiments on diverse VLM backbones and multimodal benchmarks show consistent gains in spatial grounding and visual reasoning.","absKo":"Rotary Position Embedding (RoPE)는 large language model에서 널리 사용되지만, vision-language model (VLM)에 적용하면 text와 image의 position index를 결합하여 가짜 cross-modal relative-position bias를 유발할 수 있다. 우리는 cross-modal positional disentanglement를 정량화하기 위해 Per-Token Distance (PTD)를 제안하고, $\\mathrm{PTD}=0$이 RoPE가 유도하는 geometric attention bias를 제거하기 위한 충분조건임을 증명한다. 이 기준에 따라 우리는 Circle-RoPE를 도입하는데, 이는 2D image-token coordinate를 text position axis에 직교하는 annulus로 재매핑하여, 각 text token이 모든 image token과 동일한 거리에 놓이면서도 image 내부의 spatial structure는 보존되는 cone-like geometry를 만든다. 또한 우리는 layer 간에 RoPE 변형을 번갈아 적용해 robustness를 높이는 Alternating Geometry Encoding (AGE)를 제안하며, 다양한 VLM backbone과 multimodal benchmark에서 수행한 실험은 spatial grounding과 visual reasoning에서 일관된 향상을 보여준다."},{"id":"64379","en":"ALSO: Adversarial Online Strategy Optimization for Social Agents","ko":"ALSO: 소셜 에이전트를 위한 적대적 온라인 전략 최적화","authors":"Xiang Li, Liping Yi, Mingze Kong, Min Zhang, Zhongxiang Dai, Qinghua Hu","pos":"#2300","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=OAvNOSbhwL","abs":"<p>Social simulation provides a compelling testbed for studying social intelligence, where agents interact through multi-turn dialogues under evolving contexts and strategically adapting opponents. Such environments are inherently non-stationary, requiring agents to dynamically adjust their strategies over time. However, most Large Language Model (LLM) based social agents rely on static personas, while existing approaches for enhancing social intelligence, such as offline reinforcement learning or external planners, are ill-suited to these settings, typically assuming stationarity and incurring substantial training overhead. To bridge this gap, we propose <strong>ALSO</strong> (<strong>A</strong>dversarial on<strong>L</strong>ine <strong>S</strong>trategy <strong>O</strong>ptimization), the first framework for online strategy optimization in multi-agent social simulation. ALSO advances social adaptation through two key contributions. (1) ALSO formulates multi-turn interaction as an adversarial bandit problem, where combinations of static personas and dynamic strategy instructions are treated as arms, providing a principled solution to non-stationarity without relying on environmental stability assumptions. (2) To predict rewards and generalize sparse feedback in multi-turn dialogues, ALSO introduces a lightweight neural surrogate to predict rewards from interaction histories, enabling sample-efficient exploration and continuous online adaptation. Experiments on the Sotopia benchmark demonstrate that ALSO consistently outperforms static baselines and existing optimization methods in dynamic environments, validating the effectiveness of adversarial online strategy optimization for building robust social agents. The codes of ALSO are available at  https://anonymous.4open.science/r/ALSO-67D5/</p>","absKo":"<p>Social simulation은 사회적 지능을 연구하기 위한 매력적인 testbed를 제공한다. 여기서 agent들은 변화하는 context와 전략적으로 적응하는 상대를 상대로 여러 turn에 걸친 대화를 수행한다. 이러한 환경은 본질적으로 non-stationary이므로, agent는 시간에 따라 전략을 동적으로 조정해야 한다. 그러나 대부분의 Large Language Model(LLM) 기반 social agent는 정적인 persona에 의존하며, offline reinforcement learning이나 external planner 같은 기존 사회적 지능 향상 방법은 이러한 설정에 부적합하다. 이들 방법은 대체로 stationarity를 가정하고 상당한 학습 오버헤드를 초래하기 때문이다. 이 격차를 메우기 위해, 우리는 multi-agent social simulation에서 online strategy optimization을 위한 최초의 framework인 <strong>ALSO</strong>(<strong>A</strong>dversarial on<strong>L</strong>ine <strong>S</strong>trategy <strong>O</strong>ptimization)를 제안한다. ALSO는 두 가지 핵심 기여를 통해 social adaptation을 진전시킨다. (1) ALSO는 multi-turn interaction을 adversarial bandit 문제로 정식화하며, static persona와 dynamic strategy instruction의 조합을 arm으로 취급하여, 환경의 안정성 가정에 의존하지 않고 non-stationarity에 대한 원칙적인 해법을 제공한다. (2) multi-turn dialogue에서 reward를 예측하고 sparse feedback을 일반화하기 위해, ALSO는 interaction history로부터 reward를 예측하는 경량 neural surrogate를 도입하여 sample-efficient exploration과 지속적인 online adaptation을 가능하게 한다. Sotopia benchmark에서의 실험은 ALSO가 동적 환경에서 static baseline과 기존 optimization 방법보다 일관되게 우수함을 보여주며, 견고한 social agent를 구축하기 위한 adversarial online strategy optimization의 효과를 입증한다. ALSO의 코드는 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/ALSO-67D5/ 에서 확인할 수 있다</p>"},{"id":"61950","en":"Scaling Long-Horizon Agent via Context Folding","ko":"Context Folding으로 long-horizon agent 확장","authors":"Weiwei Sun, Lu Miao, Zhan Ling, Kang Liu, Xuesong Yao, Yiming Yang, Jiecao Chen","pos":"#3408","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=lNRgWoGfYg","abs":"<p>Large language model (LLM) agents are fundamentally constrained by context length on long-horizon tasks. Existing agent frameworks usually rely on manually defined context engineering pipelines, such as multi-agent or post-hoc summary. We introduce Context Folding, a framework that empowers agents to actively manage their working context. An agent can procedurally branch into a sub-trajectory to handle a subtask and then fold it upon completion, collapsing the intermediate steps while retaining a concise summary of the outcome. To make this behavior learnable, we propose FoldPO, an end-to-end reinforcement learning framework with specific process rewards to encourage effective task decomposition and context management. On complex long-horizon tasks, our agent matches the performance of baselines while using an active context up to 10x smaller, and significantly outperforms models constrained to the same context size.</p>","absKo":"<p>대규모 언어 모델(LLM) 에이전트는 장기 지평(long-horizon) 태스크에서 본질적으로 context length의 제약을 받는다. 기존 에이전트 프레임워크는 보통 multi-agent나 post-hoc summary 같은 수동으로 정의된 context engineering pipeline에 의존한다. 우리는 에이전트가 자신의 작업 context를 능동적으로 관리할 수 있게 하는 프레임워크인 Context Folding을 제안한다. 에이전트는 절차적으로 subtask를 처리하기 위해 sub-trajectory로 분기한 뒤, 완료 시 이를 fold하여 중간 단계를 접어 넣고 결과의 간결한 요약만 유지할 수 있다. 이러한 동작을 학습 가능하게 만들기 위해, 효과적인 task decomposition과 context 관리를 유도하는 특정 process reward를 포함한 end-to-end reinforcement learning 프레임워크 FoldPO를 제안한다. 복잡한 long-horizon 태스크에서 우리의 에이전트는 active context를 최대 10배 더 작게 사용하면서도 baseline과 동등한 성능을 보였고, 동일한 context 크기로 제한된 모델들보다 유의미하게 뛰어난 성능을 보였다.</p>"},{"id":"61829","en":"Contrastive Weak-to-Strong Generalization","ko":"약한→강한 대조 학습 일반화","authors":"Houcheng Jiang, Junfeng Fang, Jiaxin Wu, Tianyu Zhang, Chen Gao, Xiang Wang, Xiangnan He, Yang Deng","pos":"#3410","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=maOM1OWNZ6","abs":"<p>Weak-to-strong generalization provides a promising paradigm for scaling large language models (LLMs) by training stronger models on samples from aligned weaker ones, without requiring human feedback or explicit reward modeling. However, its robustness and generalization are hindered by the noise and biases in weak-model outputs, which limit its applicability in practice. To address this challenge, we leverage implicit rewards, which approximate explicit rewards through log-likelihood ratios, and reveal their structural equivalence with Contrastive Decoding (CD), a decoding strategy shown to reduce noise in LLM generation. Building on this connection, we propose \\textbf{Contrastive Weak-to-Strong Generalization (ConG)}, a framework that employs contrastive decoding between pre- and post-alignment weak models to generate higher-quality samples. This approach enables more reliable capability transfer, denoising, and improved robustness, substantially mitigating the limitations of traditional weak-to-strong methods. Empirical results across different model families confirm consistent improvements, demonstrating the generality and effectiveness of ConG. Taken together, our findings highlight the potential of ConG to advance weak-to-strong generalization and provide a promising pathway toward AGI. Our code is available at: \\url{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/ConG/}</p>","absKo":"Weak-to-strong generalization은 human feedback이나 명시적 reward modeling 없이, 정렬된 더 약한 모델이 생성한 sample로 stronger model을 학습시켜 large language model (LLM)을 확장하는 유망한 패러다임을 제공한다. 그러나 weak model output의 noise와 bias는 그 견고성과 일반화를 저해하며, 이는 실제 적용 가능성을 제한한다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해 우리는 log-likelihood ratio를 통해 explicit reward를 근사하는 implicit reward를 활용하고, 이것이 LLM 생성에서 noise를 줄이는 것으로 알려진 decoding 전략인 Contrastive Decoding (CD)과 구조적으로 동등함을 밝힌다. 이 연결을 바탕으로 우리는 사전 정렬 전후의 weak model 사이에서 contrastive decoding을 수행해 더 높은 품질의 sample을 생성하는 \\textbf{Contrastive Weak-to-Strong Generalization (ConG)}을 제안한다. 이 접근은 보다 신뢰할 수 있는 capability transfer, denoising, 향상된 robustness를 가능하게 하며, 전통적인 weak-to-strong 방법의 한계를 크게 완화한다. 서로 다른 model family 전반의 실험 결과는 일관된 성능 향상을 확인해 주며, ConG의 일반성과 효과성을 보여준다. 종합하면, 우리의 결과는 weak-to-strong generalization을 발전시킬 ConG의 잠재력을 강조하며 AGI를 향한 유망한 경로를 제공한다. 코드는 다음에서 확인할 수 있다: \\url{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/ConG/}</p>"},{"id":"63270","en":"Sparser, Faster, Lighter Transformer Language Models","ko":"더 희소하고, 빠르고, 가벼운 Transformer 언어 모델","authors":"Edoardo Cetin, Stefano Peluchetti, Emilio Castillo, Akira Naruse, Mana Murakami, Llion Jones","pos":"#3602","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=YXEXsGHwpq","abs":"<p>Scaling autoregressive large language models (LLMs) has had an unprecedented impact, but at vast computational costs. In this work, we tackle these costs by leveraging unstructured sparsity within an LLM's feedforward layers, which account for the majority of its parameters and execution FLOPs. To achieve this, we rework how computation is done on modern GPUs when sparsity is detected, introducing a set of new CUDA and Triton kernels that minimize computation and memory overheads during LLM inference and training. To substantiate our gains, we provide a quantitative study of LLM sparsity, demonstrating that simple L1 regularization can induce over 99% sparsity with negligible impact on downstream performance. When paired with our kernels, we show that these sparsity levels translate into substantial throughput, energy efficiency, and memory usage benefits that increase with model scale. The code and kernels shared with this submission will be released under an open-source license to promote adoption and future research to turn sparsity into a new practical axis for the efficiency and scalability of modern foundation models.</p>","absKo":"<p>Autoregressive large language models (LLMs)의 스케일링은 전례 없는 영향을 가져왔지만, 막대한 computational cost를 수반한다. 본 연구에서는 파라미터와 execution FLOPs의 대부분을 차지하는 LLM의 feedforward layer 내 unstructured sparsity를 활용하여 이러한 비용을 줄이고자 한다. 이를 위해 sparsity가 감지될 때 현대 GPU에서 computation이 수행되는 방식을 재구성하고, LLM inference와 training 동안 computation 및 memory overhead를 최소화하는 새로운 CUDA 및 Triton kernel 집합을 도입한다. 우리의 이점을 입증하기 위해 LLM sparsity에 대한 정량적 연구를 제시하며, 단순한 L1 regularization만으로 downstream performance에 거의 영향 없이 99% 이상의 sparsity를 유도할 수 있음을 보인다. 또한 이러한 kernel과 결합했을 때, 이러한 sparsity 수준이 모델 규모가 커질수록 더욱 증가하는 throughput, energy efficiency, memory usage 개선으로 이어짐을 보여준다. 본 제출물과 함께 공유되는 코드와 kernel은 오픈소스 라이선스로 공개되어 sparsity를 현대 foundation model의 효율성과 scalability를 위한 새로운 실용적 축으로 전환하려는 채택과 후속 연구를 촉진할 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"64454","en":"Ratio-Variance Regularized Policy Optimization","ko":"비율-분산 정규화 정책 최적화","authors":"Yu Luo, Shuo Han, Yihan Hu, Lei Lv, Huaping Liu, Fuchun Sun, Jianye Hao, Dong Li","pos":"#4015","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=NT4Cz09S4w","abs":"Standard on-policy reinforcement learning relies on heuristic clipping to enforce trust regions, but this mechanism imposes a severe cost by indiscriminately truncating high-return yet high-divergence updates. We demonstrate that explicitly constraining the *policy ratio **variance*** provides a principled local approximation to trust-region constraints, eliminating the need for binary hard clipping. By acting as a distributional ''soft brake'', this approach preserves critical gradient signals from novel discoveries while naturally down-weighting and enabling the reuse of stale, off-policy data. We introduce **R$^2$VPO** (Ratio-Variance Regularized Policy Optimization), which implements this constraint via a primal–dual optimization framework. Extensive evaluations across $7$ LLM scales, spanning both fast and slow reasoning paradigms, and $10$ robotic control tasks demonstrate the generality of the proposed approach. R$^2$VPO achieves substantial performance gains on mathematical reasoning benchmarks, with particularly pronounced improvements on smaller models, while significantly improving sample efficiency. Furthermore, it consistently outperforms PPO baselines in continuous control domains, particularly in sparse-reward and dynamic environments. Together, these findings establish ratio-variance regularization as a principled foundation for stable and data-efficient policy optimization.","absKo":"표준 on-policy reinforcement learning은 trust region을 강제하기 위해 heuristic clipping에 의존하지만, 이 메커니즘은 높은 return과 높은 divergence를 동시에 갖는 update를 무차별적으로 절단함으로써 심각한 비용을 초래한다. 우리는 *policy ratio **variance***를 명시적으로 제약하는 것이 trust-region 제약에 대한 원리적인 local approximation을 제공하여 binary hard clipping이 필요 없음을 보인다. 분포적 ''soft brake''로 작동함으로써, 이 접근은 새로운 발견에서 얻어진 중요한 gradient signal을 보존하는 동시에, 오래된 off-policy data를 자연스럽게 저감하고 재사용할 수 있게 한다. 우리는 이 제약을 primal-dual optimization framework를 통해 구현하는 **R$^2$VPO** (Ratio-Variance Regularized Policy Optimization)를 제안한다. 빠른 reasoning과 느린 reasoning paradigm을 모두 아우르는 7개의 LLM scale과 10개의 robotic control task에 대한 광범위한 평가 결과, 제안 방식의 일반성이 입증되었다. R$^2$VPO는 수학적 reasoning benchmark에서 상당한 성능 향상을 달성했으며, 특히 작은 모델에서 개선 폭이 두드러졌고 sample efficiency도 크게 향상시켰다. 더 나아가 continuous control domain, 특히 sparse-reward 및 dynamic environment에서 PPO baseline을 일관되게 능가했다. 종합하면, 이러한 결과는 ratio-variance regularization이 안정적이고 data-efficient한 policy optimization을 위한 원리적인 기반임을 확립한다."},{"id":"66174","en":"Are Tools Always Beneficial? Learning to Invoke Tools Adaptively for Dual-Mode Multimodal LLM Reasoning","ko":"도구는 항상 유익한가? 이중 모드 멀티모달 LLM 추론을 위한 적응적 도구 호출 학습","authors":"Qinghe Ma, Zhen Zhao, Yiming Wu, Jian Zhang, LEI BAI, Yinghuan Shi","pos":"#2206","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=66H4jMUzft","abs":"<p>Tool-augmented reasoning has emerged as a promising direction for enhancing the reasoning capabilities of multimodal large language models (MLLMs). However, existing studies mainly focus on enabling models to perform tool invocation, while neglecting the necessity of invoking tools. We argue that tool usage is not always beneficial, as redundant or inappropriate invocations largely increase reasoning overhead and even mislead model predictions. To address this issue, we introduce AutoTool, a model that adaptively decides whether to invoke tools according to the characteristics of each query. Within a reinforcement learning framework, we design an explicit dual-mode reasoning strategy with mode-specific reward functions to guide the model toward producing accurate responses. Moreover, to prevent premature bias toward a single reasoning mode, AutoTool jointly explores and balances tool-assisted and text-centric reasoning throughout training, and promotes free exploration in later stages. Extensive experiments demonstrate that AutoTool exhibits outstanding performance and high efficiency, yielding a 21.8\\% accuracy gain on V* benchmark compared to the base model, and a 44.9\\% improvement in efficiency over existing tool-augmented methods on POPE benchmark. Code is available in the supplementary material.</p>"},{"id":"60697","en":"Memory is Reconstructed, Not Retrieved:  Graph Memory for LLM Agents","ko":"Memory는 검색되는 것이 아니라 재구성된다: LLM Agent를 위한 Graph Memory","authors":"Shuo Ji, yibo li, Bryan Hooi","pos":"#2817","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=xRVWftS3ES","abs":"Despite recent progress, LLM agents still struggle with reasoning over long interaction histories. While current memory-augmented agents rely on a static ``retrieve-then-reason'' paradigm, this rigid pipeline design prevents them from dynamically adapting memory access to intermediate evidence discovered during inference. To bridge this gap, we propose MRAgent, a framework that combines an associative memory graph with an active reconstruction mechanism. We represent memory as a Cue–Tag–Content graph, where associative tags serve as semantic bridges connecting fine-grained cues to memory contents. Operating on this structure, our active reconstruction mechanism integrates LLM reasoning directly into memory access, allowing the agent to iteratively explore and prune retrieval paths based on accumulated evidence. This ensures that memory retrieval is dynamically adapted to the  reasoning context while avoiding combinatorial explosion caused by unconstrained expansion. Experiments on the LoCoMo benchmark  and LongMemEval benchmark  demonstrate significant improvements over strong baselines (up to $23\\\\%$), while substantially reducing retrieval cost, highlighting the effectiveness of active and associative reconstruction for long-horizon memory reasoning.","absKo":"최근의 진전에도 불구하고, LLM agents는 여전히 긴 interaction history에 대한 reasoning에 어려움을 겪는다. 현재의 memory-augmented agents는 정적인 ``retrieve-then-reason'' 패러다임에 의존하는데, 이러한 경직된 pipeline 설계는 inference 중 발견된 중간 근거에 맞추어 memory access를 동적으로 조정하지 못하게 한다. 이 간극을 메우기 위해, 우리는 associative memory graph와 active reconstruction mechanism을 결합한 MRAgent를 제안한다. 우리는 memory를 Cue–Tag–Content graph로 표현하며, 여기서 associative tag는 세밀한 cues와 memory contents를 연결하는 semantic bridge 역할을 한다. 이 구조 위에서 동작하는 active reconstruction mechanism은 LLM reasoning을 memory access에 직접 통합하여, 누적된 evidence에 기반해 agent가 retrieval path를 반복적으로 탐색하고 가지치기할 수 있게 한다. 이는 무제한 확장으로 인한 combinatorial explosion을 피하면서, memory retrieval이 reasoning context에 맞추어 동적으로 적응하도록 보장한다. LoCoMo benchmark와 LongMemEval benchmark에서의 실험은 강력한 baselines에 비해 최대 $23\\\\%$의 유의미한 향상을 보이는 동시에 retrieval cost를 크게 줄여, long-horizon memory reasoning을 위한 active 및 associative reconstruction의 효과를 보여준다."},{"id":"63795","en":"Aligning Tree-Search Policies with Fixed Token Budgets in Test-Time Scaling of LLMs","ko":"LLM의 test-time scaling에서 고정 토큰 예산에 맞춘 tree-search policy 정렬","authors":"Sora Miyamoto, Daisuke Oba, Naoaki Okazaki","pos":"#2204","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=TgaVuBX8dx","abs":"<p>Tree-search decoding is an effective form of test-time scaling for large language models (LLMs), but real-world deployment imposes a fixed per-query token budget that varies across settings. Existing tree-search policies are largely budget-agnostic, treating the budget as a termination condition, which can lead to late-stage over-branching or premature termination. We propose Budget-Guided MCTS (BG-MCTS), a tree-search decoding algorithm that aligns its search policy with the remaining token budget: it starts with broad exploration, then prioritizes refinement and answer completion as the budget depletes while reducing late-stage branching from shallow nodes. BG-MCTS consistently outperforms budget-agnostic tree-search baselines across different budgets on MATH500 and AIME24/25 with open-weight LLMs.</p>","absKo":"<p>Tree-search decoding은 대규모 language model (LLM)의 test-time scaling에 효과적인 형태지만, 실제 배포에서는 설정마다 달라지는 query당 고정 token budget이 존재한다. 기존 tree-search policy는 대체로 budget에 구애받지 않으며, budget을 종료 조건으로만 취급해 후반부의 과도한 branching 또는 조기 종료를 유발할 수 있다. 우리는 Budget-Guided MCTS (BG-MCTS)를 제안한다. 이는 남은 token budget에 검색 policy를 맞추는 tree-search decoding algorithm으로, 초기에는 넓게 탐색하고 budget이 줄어들수록 정제와 답 완성을 우선하며 shallow node에서의 후반 branching을 줄인다. BG-MCTS는 open-weight LLM을 사용한 MATH500과 AIME24/25에서 서로 다른 budget 조건 전반에 걸쳐 budget-agnostic tree-search baseline보다 일관되게 우수한 성능을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"62741","en":"Confidence and Difficulty-Adaptive Policy Optimization for LLM Reasoning","ko":"LLM Reasoning을 위한 Confidence 및 난이도 적응형 Policy Optimization","authors":"(Andrew) Zhanke Zhou, Xiangyu Lu, Chentao Cao, Brando Miranda, Tongliang Liu, Bo Han, Sanmi Koyejo","pos":"#2113","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=dnpLavxTXv","abs":"<p>RL with verifiable rewards can substantially improve LLM reasoning, yet standard GRPO-style training often uses uniform sampling and near-uniform weighting, leading to inefficient computation allocation. We study GRPO by tracking token log-probabilities, group-normalized advantages, and induced token-level update weights. This reveals three recurring dynamics: probability inflation, advantage contraction as accuracy rises, and hierarchical convergence, where easy questions quickly saturate while hard questions remain discovery-limited due to rare correct rollouts. These findings imply that the benefit of each update depends strongly on both question difficulty and the model’s current competence. Motivated by this, we propose Confidence and Difficulty-adaptive Policy Optimization (CoDaPO), which assigns each question a bounded value from rollout confidence and empirical difficulty, then uses it to reweight policy updates and resample high-value questions within minibatches to increase discovery under a fixed compute budget. Across seven benchmarks, CoDaPO consistently improves accuracy over other RL methods.</p>","absKo":"verifiable reward를 사용하는 RL은 LLM reasoning을 상당히 향상시킬 수 있지만, standard GRPO-style training은 종종 uniform sampling과 near-uniform weighting을 사용하여 계산 자원을 비효율적으로 배분한다. 우리는 token log-probability, group-normalized advantage, 그리고 그로부터 유도된 token-level update weight를 추적하여 GRPO를 연구한다. 그 결과 세 가지 반복적인 dynamic이 드러난다: probability inflation, 정확도가 올라감에 따른 advantage contraction, 그리고 hierarchical convergence로서, 쉬운 질문은 빠르게 포화되는 반면 어려운 질문은 드문 correct rollout 때문에 discovery-limited 상태로 남는다. 이러한 발견은 각 update의 이점이 question difficulty와 현재 model competence 모두에 크게 의존함을 시사한다. 이에 착안하여 우리는 Confidence and Difficulty-adaptive Policy Optimization(CoDaPO)을 제안한다. CoDaPO는 rollout confidence와 empirical difficulty로부터 각 question에 bounded value를 할당한 뒤, 이를 사용하여 policy update를 재가중하고 minibatch 내에서 high-value question을 재샘플링함으로써 고정된 compute budget 하에서 discovery를 증가시킨다. 7개의 benchmark 전반에서 CoDaPO는 다른 RL method보다 일관되게 정확도를 향상시킨다.</p>"},{"id":"65862","en":"Less Is More: Elevating RAG via Performance-Driven Context Compression","ko":"적을수록 좋다: 성능 기반 문맥 압축을 통한 RAG 향상","authors":"Ziqiang Cui, Yunpeng Weng, Xing Tang, Peiyang Liu, Shiwei Li, Bowei He, Jiamin Chen, Yansen Zhang, xiuqiang He, Rui Zhang, Chen Ma","pos":"#4605","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=9LtTZQZxgd","abs":"<p>Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) has emerged as a promising paradigm for improving the timeliness of knowledge updates and the factual accuracy of large language models. However, incorporating a large volume of retrieved documents significantly increases input length, leading to prohibitive computational costs. Existing compression approaches often compromise task performance, primarily due to their reliance on predefined heuristics. These heuristics fail to ensure that the compressed context is conducive to the generation tasks. To address these limitations, we propose CORE-RAG, a novel framework for context compression in RAG systems.  CORE eliminates reliance on proxy heuristics through a performance-driven learning framework, which directy utilizes task performance as a feedback signal to iteratively refine the compressor policy.  Prior to this optimization process, we incorporate a knowledge distillation phase to initialize the compressor with a robust policy. Extensive experiments demonstrate the superiority of our approach. At a high compression ratio of 3\\%, CORE not only avoids performance degradation but also improves the average Exact Match (EM) score by 3.3 points compared to using full documents. Our code is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/CORE-28B4.</p>"},{"id":"66346","en":"The Shadow Price of Reasoning:  Economic Perspective on Optimal Budget Allocation for LLMs","ko":"추론의 그림자 가격: LLM 최적 예산 배분에 대한 경제적 관점","authors":"Xu Wan, Speed Zhu, Jianwei Cai, Guang Chen, XiMing Huang, Wiggin Zhou, Mingyang Sun","pos":"#1701","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=4VKHyt93NW","abs":"<p>Inference-time scaling has emerged as a critical avenue for enhancing Large Language Model performance, yet real-world deployment is bound by strict computational budgets. In this work, we formulate inference budget allocation as a global constrained optimization problem governed by economic principles. By modeling reasoning utility as an S-shaped function, we derive a theoretical optimal policy based on a global \\textit{shadow price} that dynamically equilibrates resource scarcity.     Based on this theory, we propose Difficulty-Aware Budget Allocation (DABA), a market-based mechanism that numerically solves for the exact market-clearing price. Unlike standard methods, DABA implements a Lambert W policy to execute strategic abandonment, sacrificing insolvent tasks to redistribute critical computational resources to solvable complex queries.     Extensive experiments on mathematical reasoning benchmarks demonstrate that DABA significantly improves the Pareto frontier of cost versus accuracy. In resource-scarce regimes, DABA achieves up to a 3 times improvement in global accuracy compared to uniform allocation.</p>"},{"id":"64975","en":"Bridging the Grounding Gap in VideoQA via Typed Memory for Language-based Belief-State Reasoning","ko":"VideoQA에서 Grounding 간극 연결: 언어 기반 Belief-State 추론을 위한 Typed Memory","authors":"Saman Forouzandeh, Wei Peng, Xinghuo Yu, Mahdi Jalili","pos":"#1102","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=IBLJ5MNcgy","abs":"VideoQA models can be accurate yet often fail to align answers with the correct video segments (the \\emph{grounding gap}). We introduce \\textbf{LINGUA} (\\textbf{L}anguage-based \\textbf{IN}ference for \\textbf{G}rounded Video \\textbf{U}nderstanding \\textbf{A}gent), a memory-based agent that performs grounded VideoQA by reasoning in an explicit \\emph{linguistic belief state}. LINGUA uses five mechanisms: (1) event-driven perception (retains 8--12\\% of frames while preserving 94\\% of question-relevant events); (2) typed memory for episodic narratives, semantic affordances, and procedural scripts; (3) Belief-Action-Verification loops with postcondition and temporal checks; (4) meta reflection with contrastive refinement; and (5) Bayesian reliability tracking for continual learning without gradient updates. Built with Gemma3-4B (Ollama, 4-bit), LINGUA outperforms strong baselines on five VideoQA benchmarks, reaching 82.4\\% on NExT-QA and 42.3\\% Acc@GQA on NExT-GQA (answer + IoU$\\geq$0.5 temporal localization), while running 2.6$\\times$ faster than dense-frame methods. In continual learning over 100 videos, accuracy rises from 45.2\\% (first 10) to 61.8\\% (last 10) without catastrophic forgetting, indicating online adaptation via memory refinement."},{"id":"64419","en":"Bridging Local–Global Dissonance: Learning from Compressive Measurements for Hyperspectral Reconstruction","ko":"지역-전역 불협화음 극복: 초분광 재구성을 위한 압축 측정으로부터의 학습","authors":"Xian-Hua Han","pos":"#1103","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=NpebZ1xmpo","abs":"<p>Reconstructing hyperspectral images from compressive measurements is challenging due to a fundamental mismatch between locally reliable observations and globally entangled structures induced by spectral dispersion. This study formalizes this issue as a local–global dissonance in representation learning for CASSI systems. To resolve it, we propose a Hierarchical Scale-Reconciling Architecture (HSRA) that enforces local sufficiency and global consistency in a principled, scale-aware manner. HSRA combines multi-kernel token mixing, latent window interactions, and hierarchical multi-granularity spatially shifted attention to progressively reconcile physical constraints across scales. Embedded into a deep unfolding framework as a physically grounded learned prior, Extensive experiments on benchmarks demonstrate that HSRA achieves consistent and significant improvements over state-of-the-art methods.</p>","absKo":"<p>압축 측정으로부터 hyperspectral image를 복원하는 것은 spectral dispersion이 유발하는 국소적으로는 신뢰할 수 있지만 전역적으로는 얽혀 있는 구조 사이의 근본적인 불일치 때문에 어렵다. 본 연구는 이 문제를 CASSI 시스템의 representation learning에서 나타나는 local–global dissonance로 정식화한다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 local sufficiency와 global consistency를 scale-aware한 방식으로 원리적으로 강제하는 Hierarchical Scale-Reconciling Architecture(HSRA)를 제안한다. HSRA는 multi-kernel token mixing, latent window interaction, 그리고 hierarchical multi-granularity spatially shifted attention을 결합하여 물리적 제약을 scale 전반에 걸쳐 점진적으로 조화시킨다. 물리적으로 정당화된 learned prior로서 deep unfolding framework에 통합한 결과, 벤치마크에서의 광범위한 실험은 HSRA가 state-of-the-art method 대비 일관되고 유의미한 성능 향상을 달성함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"61943","en":"Vision Transformer Finetuning Benefits from Non-Smooth Components","ko":"비연속 구성 요소가 Vision Transformer fine-tuning에 주는 이점","authors":"Ambroise Odonnat, Chapel Laetitia, Romain Tavenard, Ievgen Redko","pos":"#1506","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=lTXvOhUOl2","abs":"<p>The smoothness of the transformer architecture has been extensively studied in the context of generalization, training stability, and adversarial robustness. However, its role in transfer learning remains poorly understood. In this paper, we analyze the ability of vision transformer components to adapt their outputs to changes in inputs, or, in other words, their <em>plasticity</em>. Defined as an average rate of change, it captures the sensitivity to input perturbation; in particular, a high plasticity implies low smoothness. We demonstrate through theoretical analysis and comprehensive experiments that this perspective provides principled guidance in choosing the components to prioritize during adaptation. A key takeaway for practitioners is that the high plasticity of the attention modules and feedforward layers consistently leads to better finetuning performance. Our findings depart from the prevailing assumption that smoothness is desirable, offering a novel perspective on the functional properties of transformers.</p>","absKo":"<p>transformer architecture의 smoothness는 generalization, training stability, 그리고 adversarial robustness의 맥락에서 광범위하게 연구되어 왔다. 그러나 transfer learning에서 그 역할은 아직 충분히 이해되지 않았다. 본 논문에서는 vision transformer component가 입력 변화에 맞추어 출력을 적응시키는 능력, 즉 <em>plasticity</em>를 분석한다. 평균 변화율로 정의되는 이 개념은 input perturbation에 대한 민감도를 포착하며, 특히 높은 plasticity는 낮은 smoothness를 의미한다. 우리는 이 관점이 adaptation 시 우선적으로 고려해야 할 component를 선택하는 데 원칙적인 지침을 제공함을 이론적 분석과 포괄적 실험을 통해 보인다. 실무자에게 중요한 시사점은 attention module과 feedforward layer의 높은 plasticity가 일관되게 더 나은 finetuning 성능으로 이어진다는 점이다. 우리의 결과는 smoothness가 바람직하다는 기존의 통념에서 벗어나, transformer의 functional property에 대한 새로운 관점을 제시한다.</p>"},{"id":"65596","en":"UrbanFusion: Stochastic Multimodal Fusion for Contrastive Learning of Robust Spatial Representations","ko":"UrbanFusion: 강건한 공간 표현의 대조 학습을 위한 확률적 멀티모달 융합","authors":"Dominik J. Mühlematter, Lin Che, Ye Hong, Martin Raubal, Nina Wiedemann","pos":"#1507","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=C0NCLB6ZGY","abs":"<p>Forecasting urban phenomena such as housing prices and public health indicators requires the effective integration of various geospatial data. Current methods primarily utilize task-specific models, while recent generic models for spatial representations often support only limited modalities and lack multimodal fusion capabilities. To overcome these challenges, we present UrbanFusion, a spatial representation model that features Stochastic Multimodal Fusion (SMF). The framework employs modality-specific encoders to process different types of inputs, including street view imagery, remote sensing data, cartographic maps, and points of interest (POIs) data. These multimodal inputs are integrated via a Transformer-based fusion module that learns unified representations. An extensive evaluation across 41 tasks in 56 cities worldwide demonstrates UrbanFusion’s strong generalization and predictive performance compared to state-of-the-art GeoAI models. Specifically, it 1) outperforms prior models on location-encoding, 2) allows multimodal input during inference, and 3) generalizes well to regions unseen during training. UrbanFusion can flexibly utilize any subset of available modalities for a given location during both pretraining and inference, enabling broad applicability across diverse data availability scenarios.</p>"},{"id":"65029","en":"Sparse Autoencoders for Interpretable Emotion Control in Text-to-Speech","ko":"Text-to-Speech에서 해석 가능한 감정 제어를 위한 Sparse Autoencoder","authors":"Hongfei Du, Jiacheng Shi, Sidi Lu, Gang Zhou, Ashley Gao","pos":"#1510","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Hbt2ryJgz2","abs":"<p>Integrating large language models (LLMs) into text-to-speech (TTS) systems has improved speech expressiveness, yet controllable emotional expression remains challenging. Existing approaches primarily rely on external conditioning or global activation steering, offering limited insight into how emotional variation is represented internally and restricting fine-grained control. In this work, we analyze emotion-related variation in the speech semantic hidden states of LLM-based TTS models. To this end, we leverage sparse autoencoders (SAEs) to map these representations to sparse latent features and examine their emotion-related activation patterns. Our evaluations indicate that emotional variation is distributed across multiple sparse latent features, revealing a more interpretable internal representation. Building on this observation, we introduce a feature-level intervention framework that enables targeted and bidirectional emotion induction and suppression without modifying backbone parameters. We further show that distinct latent features correlate with specific acoustic attributes (e.g., pitch), suggesting that emotional expression arises from coordinated latent contributions rather than a single global shift.</p>"},{"id":"66719","en":"SLQ: Bridging Modalities via Shared Latent Queries for Retrieval with Frozen MLLMs","ko":"SLQ: Frozen MLLM을 이용한 검색을 위해 Shared Latent Query로 모달리티를 연결","authors":"Haoran Lou, Ziyan Liu, Chunxiao Fan, Yuexin Wu, Yue Ming, Hao Wu, Kai Zuo, Yibo Chen, Xu Tang","pos":"#1511","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=12CrabKNu6","abs":"<p>Multimodal Large Language Models (MLLMs) possess intrinsic reasoning and world-knowledge capabilities, yet adapting them for dense retrieval remains challenging. Existing approaches typically rely on invasive parameter updates, such as full fine-tuning and LoRA, which risk disrupting the pre-trained semantic manifold and degrading the complex knowledge structures crucial for logical inference. To address this, we propose <strong>SLQ</strong>, a parameter-efficient tuning framework that adapts MLLMs for retrieval while keeping the backbone entirely frozen. SLQ introduces a small set of <strong>Shared Latent Queries</strong> that are appended to both text and image tokens, leveraging the model’s native causal attention to aggregate multimodal context into a unified embedding space. Furthermore, to rigorously evaluate retrieval beyond superficial pattern matching, we construct <strong>KARR-Bench</strong>, a benchmark designed for knowledge-aware reasoning retrieval. Extensive experiments demonstrate that SLQ achieves better performance compared to full fine-tuning and LoRA baselines on COCO and Flickr30K, while significantly outperforming them on KARR-Bench, validating that preserving the frozen semantic manifold via non-invasive adaptation is an effective  strategy for MLLM-based retrieval.</p>"},{"id":"61362","en":"SEPS: Semantic-Enhanced Patch Slimming Framework for Fine-Grained Cross-Modal Alignment","ko":"SEPS: Fine-Grained Cross-Modal Alignment를 위한 Semantic-Enhanced Patch Slimming Framework","authors":"Xinyu Mao, Junsi Li, Haoji Zhang, Yu Liang, Ming Sun","pos":"#1512","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=qzw67boFSq","abs":"<p>Fine-grained cross-modal alignment is pivotal for multimodal reasoning yet remains limited by Semantic Sparsity Bias—a fundamental asymmetry where dense visual signals are under-represented by sparse textual captions. This disparity leads to the inadvertent suppression of contextually vital visual regions (patch redundancy) and hinders precise concept grounding (patch ambiguity). While Multimodal Large Language Models (MLLMs) offer rich descriptive capabilities, their naive integration often induces semantic drift due to inconsistencies with sparse ground-truth captions. To systematically resolve these challenges, we present the Semantic-Enhanced Patch Slimming (SEPS) framework. Central to SEPS is a novel Dual-Granularity Semantic Calibration mechanism, which synthesizes a Holistic Visual-Linguistic Anchor from MLLMs to synergize with original sparse queries. This mechanism transforms patch selection into a semantic consensus process, ensuring that retained patches satisfy both local discriminability and global contextual integrity. Furthermore, we propose a Salience-Guided Metric Aggregation strategy to mitigate the similarity dilution effect inherent in global mean pooling, thereby amplifying highly-relevant patch-word correspondences. Extensive experiments on Flickr30K and MS-COCO datasets demonstrate that SEPS surpasses existing state-of-the-art approaches across diverse backbones, delivering significant performance gains in text-to-image retrieval tasks. The complete implementation is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/SEPS/.</p>","absKo":"<p>세밀한 cross-modal alignment는 multimodal reasoning에 핵심적이지만, 조밀한 visual signal이 희소한 textual caption에 의해 과소표현되는 근본적 비대칭인 Semantic Sparsity Bias로 인해 여전히 제약을 받는다. 이러한 불일치는 문맥적으로 중요한 visual region의 의도치 않은 억제(patch redundancy)와 정확한 concept grounding의 저해(patch ambiguity)를 초래한다. Multimodal Large Language Model(MLLMs)은 풍부한 서술 능력을 제공하지만, sparse ground-truth caption과의 불일치로 인해 이를 단순 결합하면 semantic drift가 발생하는 경우가 많다. 이러한 문제를 체계적으로 해결하기 위해 우리는 Semantic-Enhanced Patch Slimming(SEPS) framework를 제안한다. SEPS의 핵심은 새로운 Dual-Granularity Semantic Calibration 메커니즘으로, MLLMs로부터 Holistic Visual-Linguistic Anchor를 합성하여 원래의 sparse query와 시너지를 이루게 한다. 이 메커니즘은 patch selection을 semantic consensus process로 변환하여, 유지되는 patch가 local discriminability와 global contextual integrity를 모두 만족하도록 보장한다. 또한 우리는 global mean pooling에 내재한 similarity dilution effect를 완화하기 위해 Salience-Guided Metric Aggregation 전략을 제안하여, 매우 관련성 높은 patch-word correspondence를 증폭한다. Flickr30K와 MS-COCO 데이터셋에서 수행한 광범위한 실험은 SEPS가 다양한 backbone에서 기존 state-of-the-art 방법을 능가하며, text-to-image retrieval task에서 유의미한 성능 향상을 제공함을 보여준다. 전체 구현은 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/SEPS/ 에서 उपलब्ध하다.</p>"},{"id":"66020","en":"PHALAR: Phasors for Learned Musical Audio Representations","ko":"PHALAR: 학습된 음악 오디오 표현을 위한 페이저","authors":"Davide Marincione, Michele Mancusi, Giorgio Strano, Luca Cerovaz, Donato Crisostomi, Roberto Ribuoli, Emanuele Rodolà","pos":"#1513","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=7sYtYeiJan","abs":"Stem retrieval, the task of matching missing stems to a given audio submix, is a key challenge currently limited by models that discard temporal information. We introduce PHALAR, a contrastive framework achieving a relative accuracy increase of up to $\\sim 70\\%$ over the state-of-the-art while requiring $&lt;$50\\% of the parameters and a 7$\\times$ training speedup. By utilizing a Learned Spectral Pooling layer and a complex-valued head, PHALAR enforces pitch-invariant and phase-equivariant biases. PHALAR establishes new retrieval state-of-the-art across MoisesDB, Slakh, and ChocoChorales, correlating significantly higher with human coherence judgment than semantic baselines. Finally, zero-shot beat tracking and linear chord probing confirm that PHALAR captures robust musical structures beyond the retrieval task."},{"id":"63329","en":"IVQ: Structured and Lightweight Vector Quantization via Binary Hierarchical Composition Inspired by $\\textit{IChing}$","ko":"IVQ: $\\textit{주역}$에서 영감받은 이진 계층 구성을 통한 구조화된 경량 벡터 양자화","authors":"Heda Zuo, Junxian Wu, Fengjie Lu, Pei Chen, Lingyun Sun, Weitao You","pos":"#1515","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Y3cUZ8fNnu","abs":"<p>Vector Quantization (VQ) has been widely used in visual and audio representation due to its effectiveness in compressing high-dimensional signals. However, existing VQ methods often rely on large and unstructured codebooks, which leads to inefficient code utilization and frequent codebook collapse. In this paper, we propose <em>IChing</em> Vector Quantization (IVQ), a lightweight and structured vector quantization framework inspired by <em>IChing</em>. IVQ introduces binary hierarchical composition and geometric symmetry relations into the codebook design, enabling a compact set of structured codes to represent a large number of configurations while maintaining high utilization without codebook collapse. We conduct systematic comparisons between IVQ and several VQ variants mainly focusing on audio representation. Experimental results show that IVQ achieves superior quality with significantly smaller codebooks and consistently higher utilization rates. Auxiliary experiments on visual reconstruction and cross-modal alignment further validate the universality and robustness of our structured representation.</p>","absKo":"<p>Vector Quantization (VQ)는 고차원 신호를 압축하는 데 효과적이어서 visual 및 audio representation에서 널리 사용되어 왔다. 그러나 기존 VQ 방법은 대개 크고 비구조적인 codebook에 의존하며, 이는 비효율적인 code utilization과 잦은 codebook collapse로 이어진다. 본 논문에서는 <em>IChing</em>에서 영감을 받은 경량의 구조적 vector quantization framework인 <em>IChing</em> Vector Quantization (IVQ)를 제안한다. IVQ는 codebook 설계에 binary hierarchical composition과 geometric symmetry relation을 도입하여, codebook collapse 없이 높은 utilization을 유지하면서도 많은 configuration을 표현할 수 있는 compact한 structured code 집합을 가능하게 한다. 우리는 주로 audio representation에 초점을 맞춰 IVQ와 여러 VQ 변형을 체계적으로 비교한다. 실험 결과, IVQ는 훨씬 더 작은 codebook과 일관되게 더 높은 utilization rate로 우수한 quality를 달성함을 보여준다. visual reconstruction과 cross-modal alignment에 대한 보조 실험은 우리의 구조적 representation의 보편성과 강건성을 추가로 검증한다.</p>"},{"id":"65614","en":"Hyperbolic RQ-VAE enhanced Generative Recommendation with Differential-Length Codebook Strategy","ko":"차등 길이 코드북 전략을 활용한 Hyperbolic RQ-VAE 기반 생성적 추천","authors":"Aoran Zhang, Yu-Bin Yang, Yonghong Yu","pos":"#1516","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=BpVBWp3PZx","abs":"<p>Recently, the integration of large language models (LLMs) with generative recommendation (GR) has demonstrated promising potential. However, most existing GR methods adopt residual quantization to implicitly model hierarchical relationships across codebook layers in Euclidean space, which distorts the intrinsic tree-like hierarchy and leads to low codebook utilization. To address these issues, we propose a Hyperbolic RQ-VAE enhanced Generative Recommendation, namely HG-Rec. Specifically, HG-Rec enhances the residual quantization mechanism by embedding the latent discrete representations into hyperbolic space to explicitly model hierarchical relationships across codebook layers. Motivated by the exponential volume growth of hyperbolic space, we further design a differential-length codebook strategy, i.e. the codebook size follows a pyramidal structure, which aligns with the tree-like structure and effectively compresses the codebook size. Hence, benefiting from the alignment of hyperbolic geometry and codebook hierarchy, HG-Rec achieves lower collision rates, more uniform codebook usage, and less training time compared to existing methods. Extensive experiments across multiple benchmark datasets demonstrate that HG-Rec consistently achieves state-of-the-art performance. The code is available in the Supplementary Material.</p>"},{"id":"65953","en":"ArcVQ-VAE: A Spherical Vector Quantization Framework with ArcCosine Additive Margin","ko":"ArcVQ-VAE: ArcCosine 가법 마진을 갖춘 구면 벡터 양자화 프레임워크","authors":"Jaeyung Kim, YoungJoon Yoo","pos":"#1613","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=8YoP649pGC","abs":"<p>Vector Quantized Variational Autoencoder (VQ-VAE) has become a fundamental framework for learning discrete representations in image modeling. However, VQ-VAE models must tokenize entire images using a finite set of codebook vectors, and this capacity limitation restricts their ability to capture rich and diverse representations. In this paper, we propose ArcCosine Additive Margin VQ-VAE (ArcVQ-VAE), a novel vector quantization framework that introduces a spherical angular-margin prior (SAMP) for the codebook of a conventional VQ-VAE. The proposed SAMP consists of Ball-Bounded Norm Regularization, which constrains all codebook vectors within a time-dependent Euclidean ball, and ArcCosine Additive Margin Loss, which encourages greater angular separability among latent vectors. This formulation promotes more discriminative and uniformly dispersed latent representations within the constrained space, thereby enabling codebook vectors to capture richer information and leading to improved codebook utilization. Experimental results on standard image reconstruction and generation tasks show that ArcVQ-VAE outperforms baseline models in terms of reconstruction accuracy, representation diversity, and sample quality.</p>"},{"id":"62480","en":"DDP-WM: Disentangled Dynamics Prediction for Efficient World Models","ko":"DDP-WM: 효율적인 World Models를 위한 Disentangled Dynamics Prediction","authors":"Shicheng Yin, Kaixuan Yin, Weixing Chen, Yang Liu, Guanbin Li, Liang Lin","pos":"#1614","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=gEc0iJCYxw","abs":"<p>World models are essential for autonomous robotic planning. However, the substantial computational overhead of existing dense Transformer-based models significantly hinders real-time deployment. To address this efficiency-performance bottleneck, we introduce DDP-WM, a novel world model centered on the principle of Disentangled Dynamics Prediction (DDP). We hypothesize that latent state evolution in observed scenes is heterogeneous and can be decomposed into sparse primary dynamics driven by physical interactions and secondary context-driven background updates. DDP-WM realizes this decomposition through an architecture that integrates efficient historical processing with dynamic localization to isolate primary dynamics. By employing a cross-attention mechanism for background updates, the framework optimizes resource allocation and provides a smooth optimization landscape for planners. Extensive experiments demonstrate that DDP-WM achieves superior efficiency and performance across diverse tasks, including navigation, precise tabletop manipulation, and complex deformable or multi-body interactions. Specifically, on the challenging Push-T task, DDP-WM achieves an approximately 9 times inference speedup and improves the MPC success rate from 90% to 98% compared to state-of-the-art dense models.</p>","absKo":"<p>World model은 자율 로봇 planning에 필수적이다. 그러나 기존 dense Transformer-based model의 상당한 계산 오버헤드는 real-time deployment를 크게 저해한다. 이러한 efficiency-performance 병목을 해결하기 위해, 우리는 Disentangled Dynamics Prediction (DDP) 원리에 기반한 새로운 world model인 DDP-WM을 제안한다. 우리는 관측된 scene에서 latent state evolution이 이질적이며, 물리적 상호작용에 의해 구동되는 sparse primary dynamics와 context-driven secondary background update로 분해될 수 있다고 가정한다. DDP-WM은 efficient historical processing과 dynamic localization을 통합하는 architecture를 통해 이러한 분해를 구현하여 primary dynamics를 분리한다. background update에는 cross-attention mechanism을 사용함으로써, framework는 resource allocation을 최적화하고 planner에게 매끄러운 optimization landscape를 제공한다. 광범위한 실험은 DDP-WM이 navigation, 정밀 tabletop manipulation, 복잡한 deformable 또는 multi-body interaction을 포함한 다양한 task에서 우수한 efficiency와 performance를 달성함을 보여준다. 특히 challenging Push-T task에서 DDP-WM은 state-of-the-art dense model 대비 inference speed를 약 9배 향상시키고 MPC success rate를 90%에서 98%로 높인다.</p>"},{"id":"65144","en":"Efficient Code Analysis via Graph-Guided Large Language Models","ko":"그래프 기반 Large Language Model을 통한 효율적 코드 분석","authors":"Hang Gao, Tao Peng, Baoquan Cui, Hong Huang, Fengge Wu, Zhao Junsuo, Jian Zhang","pos":"#1615","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=GNieZ8Z5V5","abs":"<p>Large Language Models (LLMs) have significantly advanced code analysis tasks, yet they struggle to detect malicious behaviors fragmented across files, whose intricate dependencies easily get lost in the vast amount of benign code. We therefore propose a graph-centric attention acquisition pipeline that enhances LLMs' ability to localize malicious behavior. The approach parses a project into a code graph, uses an LLM to encode nodes with semantic and structural signals, and trains a Graph Neural Network (GNN) under sparse supervision. The GNN performs an initial detection, and by interpreting these predictions, identifies key code sections that are most likely to contain malicious behavior. These influential regions are then used to guide the LLM's attention for in-depth analysis. This strategy significantly reduces interference from irrelevant context while maintaining low annotation costs. Extensive experiments show that the method consistently outperforms existing approaches on multiple public and custom datasets, highlighting its potential for practical deployment in software security scenarios.</p>"},{"id":"63258","en":"Efficient Multi-modal Dataset Distillation via Analytic Parameter Matching","ko":"해석적 파라미터 매칭을 통한 효율적 멀티모달 데이터셋 증류","authors":"Deyu Bo, Xinchao Wang","pos":"#1616","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Yh4dMR5mJ0","abs":"Multi-modal dataset distillation (MDD) seeks to compress large-scale multi-modal datasets into a compact set of synthetic pairs. Existing methods employ a dual-trajectory matching framework to align the teacher and student models within each modality. While effective, this paradigm incurs non-negligible memory and computational overhead due to the checkpoint storage and bi-level optimization over synthetic data. To address these limitations, we propose analytic parameter matching (APM), which theoretically derives the analytic parameters of modal projectors to replace the inner-loop optimization, and then aligns the analytic projector parameters of teacher and student models. APM offers two key advantages: (1) it replaces checkpoint-intensive storage with only two cached matrices, significantly reducing memory consumption; and (2) it computes analytic parameters in a single forward pass, thereby avoiding costly bi-level optimization. Empirically, APM achieves up to 65$\\times$ storage reduction and 9.6$\\times$ faster distillation, while scaling to 1,000 synthetic pairs. Extensive experiments on image-text and audio-text benchmarks demonstrate the effectiveness of APM in cross-modal retrieval tasks, \\eg, 12.8 IR@1 and 17.8 TR@1 in Flickr30k with 100 synthetic pairs. Moreover, APM exhibits notable generalization performance in cross-architecture evaluation and zero-shot classification tasks.","absKo":"Multi-modal dataset distillation (MDD)은 대규모 multi-modal datasets를 compact한 synthetic pairs 집합으로 압축하는 것을 목표로 한다. 기존 방법들은 dual-trajectory matching framework를 사용하여 각 modality 내에서 teacher와 student model을 정렬한다. 효과적이지만, 이 패러다임은 checkpoint storage와 synthetic data에 대한 bi-level optimization 때문에 무시할 수 없는 memory 및 computational overhead를 유발한다. 이러한 한계를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 analytic parameter matching (APM)을 제안한다. APM은 inner-loop optimization을 대체하기 위해 modal projector의 analytic parameters를 이론적으로 도출한 뒤, teacher와 student model의 analytic projector parameters를 정렬한다. APM은 두 가지 핵심 장점을 제공한다: (1) checkpoint-intensive storage를 두 개의 cached matrices만으로 대체하여 memory consumption을 크게 줄인다. (2) single forward pass에서 analytic parameters를 계산하므로, 비용이 큰 bi-level optimization을 피할 수 있다. 실험적으로 APM은 storage를 최대 65$\\times$까지 줄이고 distillation 속도를 9.6$\\times$ 높이면서, 1,000개의 synthetic pairs까지 확장된다. image-text 및 audio-text benchmarks에서 수행한 광범위한 실험은 cross-modal retrieval task에서 APM의 효과를 보여준다. 예를 들어 Flickr30k에서 100 synthetic pairs로 12.8 IR@1 및 17.8 TR@1을 달성한다. 더 나아가 APM은 cross-architecture evaluation과 zero-shot classification task에서도 주목할 만한 generalization 성능을 보인다."},{"id":"61492","en":"Dispersion Loss Counteracts Embedding Condensation and Improves Generalization in Small Language Models","ko":"Dispersion Loss는 Embedding Condensation을 상쇄하고 Small Language Models의 일반화를 개선한다","authors":"Chen Liu, Xingzhi Sun, Xi Xiao, Alexandre Van Tassel, Ke Xu, Kristof Reimann, Danqi Liao, Mark Gerstein, Tianyang Wang, Xiao Wang, Smita Krishnaswamy","pos":"#2106","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=pd6A7jB5D6","abs":"Large language models (LLMs) achieve remarkable performance through ever-increasing parameter counts, but scaling incurs steep computational costs. To better understand LLM scaling, we study representational differences between LLMs and their smaller counterparts, with the goal of replicating the representational qualities of larger models in the smaller models. We observe a geometric phenomenon which we term $\\textit{\\textbf{embedding condensation}}$, where token embeddings collapse into a narrow cone-like subspace in some language models. Through systematic analyses across multiple Transformer families, we show that small models such as $\\texttt{GPT2}$ and $\\texttt{Qwen3-0.6B}$ exhibit severe condensation, whereas the larger models such as $\\texttt{GPT2-xl}$ and $\\texttt{Qwen3-32B}$ are more resistant to this phenomenon. Additional observations show that embedding condensation is not reliably mitigated by knowledge distillation from larger models. To fight against it, we formulate a dispersion loss that explicitly encourages embedding dispersion during training. Experiments demonstrate that it mitigates condensation, recovers dispersion patterns seen in larger models, and yields performance gains across 10 benchmarks. We believe this work offers a principled path toward improving smaller Transformers without additional parameters.","absKo":"대규모 언어 모델(LLM)은 점점 더 증가하는 parameter count를 통해 놀라운 성능을 달성하지만, scaling은 큰 계산 비용을 수반한다. LLM scaling을 더 잘 이해하기 위해, 우리는 LLM과 그보다 작은 counterpart 간의 표현적 차이를 연구하고, 더 큰 model의 표현적 특성을 작은 model에서 재현하는 것을 목표로 한다. 우리는 \\textit{\\textbf{embedding condensation}}이라 부르는 기하학적 현상을 관찰하는데, 여기서 token embedding이 일부 language model에서 좁은 cone-like subspace로 붕괴한다. 여러 Transformer family에 걸친 체계적 분석을 통해, \\texttt{GPT2}와 \\texttt{Qwen3-0.6B} 같은 작은 model은 심각한 condensation을 보이는 반면, \\texttt{GPT2-xl}과 \\texttt{Qwen3-32B} 같은 큰 model은 이 현상에 더 강함을 보인다. 추가 관찰은 embedding condensation이 larger model로부터의 knowledge distillation으로 안정적으로 완화되지 않음을 보여준다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 학습 중 embedding dispersion을 명시적으로 장려하는 dispersion loss를 정식화한다. 실험은 이 손실이 condensation을 완화하고, 더 큰 model에서 보이는 dispersion pattern을 회복하며, 10개 benchmark 전반에서 성능 향상을 이끈다는 것을 보여준다. 우리는 이 연구가 추가 parameter 없이 더 작은 Transformer를 개선하기 위한 원리적인 경로를 제공한다고 믿는다."},{"id":"62085","en":"CrossQ: Task-Aligned Cross-Token Conditional Quantization for Late Interaction Retrieval","ko":"CrossQ: Late Interaction 검색을 위한 태스크 정렬 Cross-Token 조건부 양자화","authors":"Rohit Kumar Salla, Manoj Saravanan, Ramya Amancherla","pos":"#3405","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=jxHF6z0S1L","abs":"<p>Late-interaction retrievers like ColBERT achieve high quality but suffer from large multi-vector indices. Standard compression minimizes token reconstruction error, while ranking depends critically on preserving scores of sparse \"winner\" tokens. We introduce CrossQ which adaptively allocates precision within documents by conditioning token codes on lightweight document context computed at indexing time (but not stored). Trained with ranking-aligned objectives that preserve candidate score distributions and protect hard-negative margins, CrossQ improves MRR@10 by +0.012 on MS MARCO and average nDCG@10 by +0.018 on BEIR over strong baselines at matched footprints (2-8 B/token). With light fine-tuning, CrossQ achieves 61x compression while narrowing the gap with full-precision ColBERT to just 2.3% MRR@10, establishing a new state-of-the-art in the latency-quality tradeoff for memory-constrained retrieval.</p>","absKo":"<p>ColBERT 같은 late-interaction retriever는 높은 품질을 달성하지만, 큰 multi-vector index라는 문제를 안고 있다. 표준 compression은 token reconstruction error를 최소화하지만, ranking은 sparse \"winner\" token의 score를 보존하는 데 결정적으로 의존한다. 우리는 indexing 시점에 계산되지만 저장되지는 않는 lightweight document context에 token code를 조건화함으로써 문서 내부에서 precision을 적응적으로 할당하는 CrossQ를 제안한다. candidate score 분포를 보존하고 hard-negative margin을 보호하는 ranking-aligned objective로 학습된 CrossQ는 동일한 footprint(2-8 B/token)에서 강력한 baseline 대비 MS MARCO에서 MRR@10을 +0.012, BEIR에서 평균 nDCG@10을 +0.018 향상시킨다. light fine-tuning을 사용하면 CrossQ는 61배 compression을 달성하면서 full-precision ColBERT와의 격차를 MRR@10 기준 2.3%까지 좁혀, memory-constrained retrieval에서 latency-quality tradeoff의 새로운 state-of-the-art를 확립한다.</p>"},{"id":"61590","en":"Geometrically Constrained Outlier Synthesis","ko":"기하 제약 Outlier Synthesis","authors":"Daniil Karzanov, Marcin Detyniecki","pos":"#4201","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=odLc0zNtyX","abs":"<p>Deep neural networks for image classification often exhibit overconfidence on out-of-distribution (OOD) samples. To address this, we introduce Geometrically Constrained Outlier Synthesis (GCOS), a training-time regularization framework aimed at improving OOD robustness during inference. GCOS addresses a limitation of prior synthesis methods by generating virtual outliers in the hidden feature space that respect the learned manifold structure of in-distribution (ID) data. The synthesis proceeds in two stages: (i) a dominant-variance subspace extracted from the training features identifies geometrically informed, off-manifold directions; (ii) a conformally-inspired shell, defined by the empirical quantiles of a nonconformity score from a calibration set, adaptively controls the synthesis magnitude to produce boundary samples. The shell ensures that generated outliers are neither trivially detectable nor indistinguishable from in-distribution data, facilitating smoother learning of robust features. This is combined with a contrastive regularization objective that promotes separability of ID and OOD samples in a chosen score space, such as Mahalanobis or energy-based. Experiments demonstrate that GCOS outperforms state-of-the-art methods using standard energy-based inference on near-OOD benchmarks, defined as tasks where outliers share the same semantic domain as in-distribution data. As an exploratory extension, the framework naturally transitions to conformal OOD inference, which translates uncertainty scores into statistically valid p-values and enables thresholds with formal error guarantees, providing a pathway toward more predictable and reliable OOD detection.</p>","absKo":"<p>이미지 분류를 위한 deep neural network는 out-of-distribution (OOD) sample에 대해 지나치게 자신감 있게 반응하는 경우가 많다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 추론 시 OOD robustness를 향상시키기 위한 training-time regularization framework인 Geometrically Constrained Outlier Synthesis (GCOS)를 제안한다. GCOS는 in-distribution (ID) data가 학습한 manifold structure를 존중하는 hidden feature space에서 virtual outlier를 생성함으로써 기존 synthesis method의 한계를 해결한다. 합성은 두 단계로 진행된다. (i) training feature에서 추출한 dominant-variance subspace가 기하학적으로 정보를 담은 off-manifold 방향을 식별한다. (ii) calibration set의 nonconformity score에 대한 empirical quantile로 정의된 conformal-inspired shell이 합성 크기를 적응적으로 제어하여 boundary sample을 생성한다. 이 shell은 생성된 outlier가 너무 쉽게 탐지되지도, 반대로 in-distribution data와 구분되지 않을 정도로 유사하지도 않도록 보장하여, 견고한 feature의 더 매끄러운 학습을 돕는다. 여기에 Mahalanobis 또는 energy-based score space와 같은 선택된 공간에서 ID와 OOD sample의 separability를 촉진하는 contrastive regularization objective를 결합한다. 실험은 GCOS가 near-OOD benchmark, 즉 outlier가 in-distribution data와 동일한 semantic domain을 공유하는 task에서 표준 energy-based inference를 사용하는 최신 방법보다 우수함을 보여준다. 탐색적 확장으로, 이 framework는 conformal OOD inference로 자연스럽게 이어지며, uncertainty score를 통계적으로 유효한 p-value로 변환하고 형식적 error guarantee를 갖는 threshold를 가능하게 하여, 더 예측 가능하고 신뢰할 수 있는 OOD detection으로 가는 경로를 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"66633","en":"RQ-MoE: Residual Quantization via Mixture of Experts for Efficient Input-Dependent Vector Compression","ko":"RQ-MoE: 효율적 입력 의존 벡터 압축을 위한 Mixture of Experts 기반 잔차 양자화","authors":"Zhengjia Zhong, Shuyan Ke, zaizhou lin, Jiaqi Song, Hongyi Lan, Hui Li","pos":"#4203","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=1wnPjWrw18","abs":"<p>Vector quantization is a fundamental tool for compressing high-dimensional embeddings, yet existing multi-codebook methods rely on static codebooks that limit expressiveness under heterogeneous data geometry. While recent dynamic quantizers like QINCo adapt codebooks to individual inputs and improve expressiveness, their strict sequential dependencies create decoding bottlenecks. We propose Residual Quantization via Mixture of Experts (RQ-MoE), a framework combining a two-level MoE with dual-stream quantization to enable input-dependent codebook adaptation for efficient vector quantization. RQ-MoE enables dynamic codebook construction and decouples instruction from quantization, facilitating parallel decoding. Theoretically, we show that standard Residual Quantization and prior dynamic methods are degenerate cases of RQ-MoE, and derive a guideline for setting expert dimensionality in RQ-MoE. Extensive experiments show that RQ-MoE achieves state-of-the-art or on-par performance in reconstruction and retrieval, while it can provide 6×–14× faster decoding than prior vector quantization methods. We anonymously provide the implementation at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/RQ-MoE.</p>"},{"id":"63527","en":"TVDRNet: Text-driven Viewpoint Optimization via Differentiable Rendering for 3D Reasoning Segmentation","ko":"TVDRNet: 3D 추론 세분화를 위한 미분 가능 렌더링 기반 텍스트 구동 시점 최적화","authors":"yu zaiyang, Changshuo Wang, Pinjie Xu, ZhangHuang, Yuan Shi, Linjun Sun, Weijun Li","pos":"#807","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=WQC09ugdju","abs":"<p>Three-dimensional (3D) reasoning segmentation aims to segment target objects based on text instructions and 3D spatial cues. Recent efforts in 3D reasoning leverage Multimodal Large Language Models (MLLMs) to bridge the gap between text and 3D data. However, since MLLMs are primarily trained on text-image pairs, directly adapting them to unstructured 3D point clouds often fails to capture implicit semantic intent and reliably localize objects. This paper introduces TVDRNet to address these challenges. Inspired by Active Vision theory, where humans selectively choose optimal viewpoints to better observe targets, TVDRNet employs a differentiable renderer to simulate this active process in 3D perception. By using text instructions as supervision to optimize intrinsic and extrinsic rendering parameters, the TVDRNet identifies the optimal viewpoints for observing the 3D scene, and therefore learning 'where to look' based on what the text instruction 'asked to find'. This process generates informative, task-relevant 2D images that are compatible with MLLMs. TVDRNet comprises: (1) the AVPL module, establishing a learnable mapping from semantics to optimal rendering parameters; and (2) the MGL module, fusing multi-modalities via semantic grouping to guide mask generation. Experiments show TVDRNet achieves SOTA performance in 3D reasoning segmentation (Reason3D, Instruct3D) and 3D visual grounding (ScanRefer).</p>","absKo":"<p>3차원(3D) reasoning segmentation은 텍스트 지시와 3D 공간 단서를 바탕으로 대상 객체를 분할하는 것을 목표로 한다. 최근 3D reasoning 연구는 텍스트와 3D 데이터 간의 간극을 메우기 위해 Multimodal Large Language Models(MLLMs)를 활용해 왔다. 그러나 MLLMs는 주로 text-image pair로 학습되기 때문에, 구조화되지 않은 3D point cloud에 직접 적응시키면 암묵적 의미 의도를 포착하고 객체를 신뢰성 있게 국소화하는 데 실패하는 경우가 많다. 본 논문은 이러한 과제를 해결하기 위해 TVDRNet을 소개한다. 인간이 목표를 더 잘 관찰하기 위해 최적의 시점을 선택하는 Active Vision 이론에 착안하여, TVDRNet은 differentiable renderer를 사용해 3D perception에서의 이 능동적 과정을 시뮬레이션한다. 텍스트 지시를 supervision으로 사용해 intrinsic 및 extrinsic rendering parameter를 최적화함으로써, TVDRNet은 3D 장면을 관찰하기 위한 최적의 시점을 찾아내고, 따라서 텍스트 지시가 \"찾으라고 요청한 것\"에 기반해 \"어디를 볼지\"를 학습한다. 이 과정은 MLLMs와 호환되는 정보성 높고 task-relevant한 2D 이미지를 생성한다. TVDRNet은 다음으로 구성된다. (1) 의미론에서 최적 rendering parameter로의 학습 가능한 매핑을 구축하는 AVPL 모듈, 그리고 (2) semantic grouping을 통해 multi-modality를 융합하여 mask 생성을 유도하는 MGL 모듈. 실험 결과 TVDRNet은 3D reasoning segmentation(Reason3D, Instruct3D)과 3D visual grounding(ScanRefer)에서 SOTA 성능을 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"66505","en":"FedHPro: Federated Hyper-Prototype Learning via Gradient Matching","ko":"FedHPro: 그래디언트 매칭을 통한 Federated Hyper-Prototype 학습","authors":"Huan Wang, Jun Shen, Haoran Li, Zhenyu Yang, Jun Yan, Ousman Manjang, Yanlong Zhai, Di Wu, Guansong Pang","pos":"#3702","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=35e16MmSL0","abs":"<p>Federated Learning (FL) enables collaborative training of distributed clients while protecting privacy. To enhance generalization capability in FL, prototype-based FL is in the spotlight, since shared global prototypes offer semantic anchors for aligning client-specific local prototypes. However, existing methods update global prototypes at the prototype-level via averaging local prototypes or refining global anchors, which often leads to semantic drift across clients and subsequently yields a misaligned global signal. To alleviate this issue, we introduce <em><strong>hyper-prototypes</strong></em>, defined by a set of learnable global class-wise prototypes to preserve underlying semantic knowledge across clients. The hyper-prototypes are optimized via gradient matching to align with class-relevant characteristics distilled directly from clients' real samples, rather than prototype-level descriptors. We further propose <em><strong>FedHPro</strong></em>, a Federated Hyper-Prototype Learning framework, to leverage hyper-prototypes to promote inter-class separability via mutual-contrastive learning with client-specific margin, while encouraging intra-class uniformity through a consistency penalty. Comprehensive experiments under diverse heterogeneous scenarios confirm that 1) hyper-prototypes produce a more semantically consistent global signal, and 2) FedHPro achieves state-of-the-art performance on several benchmark datasets.</p>"},{"id":"66233","en":"Learning Locally, Revising Globally: Global Reviser for Federated Learning with Noisy Labels","ko":"국소적으로 학습하고 전역적으로 수정하기: 노이즈 레이블을 갖는 Federated Learning을 위한 전역 수정기","authors":"Yuxin Tian, Mouxing Yang, Yuhao Zhou, Jian Wang, Qing Ye, Tongliang Liu, Gang Niu, Jiancheng Lv","pos":"#4208","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=5Zp3m9Uetz","abs":"<p>In pursuit of data privacy, federated learning (FL) collaboratively trains a global model by aggregating local models learned from decentralized data. However, FL heavily depends on high-quality labels, which are often impractical in the real world, leading to the federated label-noise (F-LN) problem. Unlike traditional noisy labels, the F-LN problem is exacerbated by the inherent heterogeneity of FL, where clients experience varying levels and types of label errors. In this study, we observe that the global model of FL exhibits slow memorization of noisy labels, suggesting its ability to maintain reliable predictions and robust representations in FL. Based on this insight, we propose a novel method termed Global Reviser for Federated Learning with Noisy Labels (FedGR) to improve the robustness of FL against the F-LN problem. Specifically, FedGR first leverages the label-noise-robust characteristics of the global model to filter and refine the noisy labels on each client using the sieving-and-refining module. Then, it regularizes local model training with the assistance of the global model through the following two modules: the globally revised exponential moving average (EMA) distillation module and the global representation regularization module. Extensive experiments on three widely used F-LN benchmarks demonstrate the superior performance of FedGR, outperforming seven state-of-the-art baselines even in complicated label-noise and data heterogeneity. The code will be released upon acceptance.</p>"},{"id":"66200","en":"Rethinking generative image pretraining: How far are we from scaling up next-pixel prediction?","ko":"생성적 이미지 사전 훈련 재고: 다음 픽셀 예측의 스케일업까지 얼마나 남았는가?","authors":"Xinchen Yan, Chen Liang, Lijun Yu, Adams Wei Yu, Yifeng Lu, Quoc Le","pos":"#2508","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=5pOlWjnGn3","abs":"<p>This paper investigates the scaling properties of autoregressive next-pixel prediction, a simple, end-to-end yet under-explored framework for unified vision models. Starting with images at resolutions of 32x32, we train a family of Transformers using IsoFlops profiles across compute budgets up to 7e19 FLOPs and evaluate three distinct target metrics: next-pixel prediction objective, ImageNet classification accuracy, and generation quality measured by Fr'echet Distance. First, optimal scaling strategy is critically task-dependent. At a fixed 32x32 resolution alone, the optimal scaling properties for image classification and image generation diverge, where generation optimal setup requires the data size grow three to five times faster than for the classification optimal setup. Second, as image resolution increases, the optimal scaling strategy indicates that the model size must grow much faster than data size. Surprisingly, by projecting our findings, we discover that the primary bottleneck is compute rather than the amount of training data. As compute continues to grow four to five times annually, we forecast the feasibility of pixel-by-pixel modeling of images within the next five years.</p>"},{"id":"64851","en":"Parallel Stochastic Gradient-Based Planning for World Models","ko":"World Model을 위한 병렬 Stochastic Gradient 기반 계획","authors":"Michael Psenka, Michael Rabbat, Aditi Krishnapriyan, Yann LeCun, Amir Bar","pos":"#110","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=J8lkAoQeYK","abs":"<p>World models simulate environment dynamics from raw sensory inputs like video. However, using them for planning can be challenging due to the vast and unstructured search space. We propose a robust and highly parallelizable planner that  leverages the differentiability of the learned world model for efficient optimization, solving long-horizon control tasks from visual input. Our method treats states as optimization variables (\"virtual states\") with soft dynamics constraints, enabling parallel computation and easier optimization. To facilitate exploration and avoid local optima, we introduce stochasticity into the states. To mitigate sensitive gradients through high-dimensional vision-based world models, we modify the gradient structure to descend towards valid plans while only requiring action-input gradients. Our approach can be viewed as a stochastic version of a non-condensed or collocation-based optimal controller. We provide theoretical justification and experiments on video-based world models, where our resulting planner outperforms existing planning algorithms like the cross-entropy method (CEM) and vanilla gradient-based optimization (GD) on long-horizon experiments, both in success rate and time to convergence.</p>"},{"id":"65468","en":"On Structured State-Space Duality","ko":"구조화된 State-Space 이중성에 대하여","authors":"Jerry Yao-Chieh Hu, Xiwen Zhang, Ali ElSheikh, Weimin Wu, Han Liu","pos":"#1309","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=DKathyl3XN","abs":"Structured \\underline{S}tate-\\underline{S}pace \\underline{D}uality (SSD)  [Dao \\&amp; Gu, ICML 2024] is an equivalence between a simple Structured \\underline{S}tate-\\underline{S}pace \\underline{M}odel (SSM) and a masked attention mechanism.  In particular, a state-space model with a scalar-times-identity state matrix is equivalent to a masked self-attention with a $1$-semiseparable causal mask. Consequently, the same sequence transformation (model) has two algorithmic realizations:  as a linear-time $O(T)$ recurrence or as a quadratic-time $O(T^2)$ attention. In this note, we formalize and generalize this duality: (i)  we extend SSD from the scalar‑identity case to general diagonal SSMs (diagonal state matrices);  (ii) we show that these diagonal SSMs match the scalar case's training complexity lower bounds while supporting richer dynamics; (iii) we establish a necessary and sufficient condition under which an SSM is equivalent to $1$-semiseparable masked attention;  and (iv) we show that such duality fails to extend to standard softmax attention due to rank explosion. Together, these results tighten bridge between recurrent SSMs and Transformers, and widen the design space for expressive yet efficient sequence models."},{"id":"62701","en":"Efficient Neural Controlled Differential Equations via Attentive Kernel Smoothing","ko":"Attentive Kernel Smoothing 기반 Efficient Neural Controlled Differential Equations","authors":"Egor Serov, Ilya Kuleshov, Alexey Zaytsev","pos":"#1400","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=e6hVbhHEXh","abs":"<p>Neural Controlled Differential Equations (Neural CDEs) provide a powerful continuous-time framework for sequence modeling, yet the roughness of the driving control path often restricts their efficiency. Standard splines introduce high-frequency variations that force adaptive solvers to take excessively small steps, driving up the Number of Function Evaluations (NFE). We propose a novel approach to Neural CDE path construction that replaces exact interpolation with Kernel and Gaussian Process (GP) smoothing, enabling explicit control over trajectory regularity. To recover details lost during smoothing, we propose an attention-based Multi-View CDE (MV-CDE) and its convolutional extension (MVC-CDE), which employ learnable queries to inform path reconstruction. This framework allows the model to distribute representational capacity across multiple trajectories, each capturing distinct temporal patterns. Empirical results demonstrate that our method, MVC-CDE with GP, achieves state-of-the-art accuracy while significantly reducing NFEs and total inference time compared to spline-based baselines.</p>","absKo":"<p>Neural Controlled Differential Equations (Neural CDEs)는 sequence modeling을 위한 강력한 continuous-time framework를 제공하지만, driving control path의 roughness가 종종 그 효율성을 제한한다. Standard spline은 고주파 변동을 도입하여 adaptive solver가 지나치게 작은 step을 밟도록 만들고, 그 결과 Number of Function Evaluations (NFE)이 증가한다. 우리는 정확한 interpolation을 Kernel 및 Gaussian Process (GP) smoothing으로 대체하여 trajectory regularity를 명시적으로 제어할 수 있게 하는, Neural CDE path construction을 위한 새로운 접근을 제안한다. smoothing 과정에서 사라진 세부 정보를 복원하기 위해 우리는 attention-based Multi-View CDE (MV-CDE)와 그 convolutional 확장판인 (MVC-CDE)를 제안하며, 이들은 learnable query를 사용해 path reconstruction을 안내한다. 이 framework는 model이 여러 trajectory에 representational capacity를 분산하도록 하며, 각 trajectory는 서로 다른 temporal pattern을 포착한다. 실험 결과는 GP를 사용한 MVC-CDE가 spline 기반 baseline과 비교해 NFE와 총 inference time을 크게 줄이면서도 state-of-the-art accuracy를 달성함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"63935","en":"GHOST: Unmasking Phantom States in Mamba2 via Grouped Hidden-state Output-aware Selection & Truncation","ko":"GHOST: grouped hidden-state output-aware selection & truncation을 통한 Mamba2의 phantom state 해명","authors":"Michael Menezes, Anastasios Kyrillidis","pos":"#1401","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=SR2RDhhnxj","abs":"<p>While Mamba2's expanded state dimension enhances temporal modeling, it incurs substantial inference overhead that saturates bandwidth during autoregressive generation. Standard pruning methods fail to address this bottleneck: unstructured sparsity leaves activations dense, magnitude-based selection ignores runtime dynamics, and gradient-based methods impose prohibitive costs. We introduce GHOST (Grouped Hidden-state Output-aware Selection and Truncation), a structured pruning framework that approximates control-theoretic balanced truncation using only forward-pass statistics. By jointly measuring controllability and observability, GHOST rivals the fidelity of gradient-based methods without requiring backpropagation. As a highlight, on models ranging from 130M to 2.7B parameters, our approach achieves a 50% state-dimension reduction with approximately 1 perplexity point increase on WikiText-2. Code is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/mamba2_ghost-7BCB/.</p>","absKo":"<p>Mamba2의 확장된 상태 차원은 시간적 모델링을 향상시키지만, 자기회귀 생성 동안 대역폭을 포화시키는 상당한 추론 오버헤드를 유발한다. 표준 프루닝 방법은 이 병목을 해결하지 못한다. 구조화되지 않은 희소성은 활성값을 여전히 조밀하게 남기고, 크기 기반 선택은 런타임 동역학을 무시하며, 그래디언트 기반 방법은 감당하기 어려운 비용을 초래한다. 우리는 순전파 통계만을 사용하여 제어이론의 balanced truncation을 근사하는 구조화된 프루닝 프레임워크인 GHOST(Grouped Hidden-state Output-aware Selection and Truncation)를 제안한다. GHOST는 제어가능성과 관측가능성을 공동으로 측정함으로써 역전파를 요구하지 않으면서도 그래디언트 기반 방법에 필적하는 충실도를 달성한다. 대표적으로, 130M에서 2.7B 파라미터에 이르는 모델들에서 우리의 접근은 WikiText-2에서 perplexity가 약 1 포인트 증가하는 수준으로 상태 차원을 50% 줄인다. 코드는 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/mamba2_ghost-7BCB/ 에서 확인할 수 있다.</p>"},{"id":"61174","en":"Improving the Performance and Learning Stability of Parallelizable RNNs Designed for Ultra-Low Power Applications","ko":"초저전력 응용을 위해 설계된 병렬화 가능 RNN의 성능 및 학습 안정성 향상","authors":"Julien Brandoit, Arthur Fyon, Damien Ernst, Guillaume Drion","pos":"#1402","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=t2bQt6M7Qh","abs":"Sequence learning is dominated by Transformers and parallelizable recurrent neural networks such as state-space models, yet learning long-term dependencies remains challenging, and state-of-the-art designs trade power consumption for performance. The Bistable Memory Recurrent Unit (BMRU) was introduced to enable hardware–software co-design of ultra-low power RNNs: quantized states with hysteresis provide persistent memory while mapping directly to analog primitives. However, BMRU performance lags behind parallelizable RNNs on complex sequential tasks. In this paper, we identify gradient blocking during state updates as a key limitation and propose a cumulative update formulation that restores gradient flow while preserving persistent memory, creating skip-connections through time. This leads to the Cumulative Memory Recurrent Unit (CMRU) and its relaxed variant, the $\\alpha$CMRU. Experiments show that the cumulative formulation dramatically improves convergence stability and reduces initialization sensitivity. The CMRU and $\\alpha$CMRU match the performance of Linear Recurrent Units (LRUs) and minimal Gated Recurrent Units (minGRUs) on standard benchmarks at small model sizes, while the CMRU retains quantized states, persistent memory, and noise-resilient dynamics essential for analog implementation.","absKo":"Sequence learning은 Transformer와 state-space model 같은 병렬화 가능한 recurrent neural network가 주도하고 있지만, long-term dependency를 학습하는 일은 여전히 어렵고, 현재의 최첨단 설계들은 성능과 전력 소모 사이에서 절충을 강요한다. Bistable Memory Recurrent Unit (BMRU)는 ultra-low power RNN의 hardware–software co-design을 가능하게 하기 위해 도입되었다. hysteresis를 갖는 quantized state는 persistent memory를 제공하면서 analog primitive에 직접 매핑된다. 그러나 BMRU의 성능은 복잡한 sequential task에서 병렬화 가능한 RNN에 미치지 못한다. 본 논문에서는 state update 동안의 gradient blocking을 핵심 한계로 규명하고, persistent memory를 보존하면서 gradient flow를 복원하는 cumulative update formulation을 제안하여 time을 가로지르는 skip-connection을 만든다. 이를 통해 Cumulative Memory Recurrent Unit (CMRU)과 그 relaxed variant인 $\\alpha$CMRU를 도출한다. 실험 결과, cumulative formulation은 convergence stability를 극적으로 향상시키고 initialization sensitivity를 줄인다. CMRU와 $\\alpha$CMRU는 작은 모델 크기의 표준 benchmark에서 Linear Recurrent Unit (LRU)과 minimal Gated Recurrent Unit (minGRU) 수준의 성능을 보이며, CMRU는 analog implementation에 필수적인 quantized state, persistent memory, 그리고 noise-resilient dynamics를 유지한다."},{"id":"62077","en":"Learning Manifold and Itô Dynamics with Branched Neural Rough Differential Equations","ko":"분기 신경 Rough 미분방정식으로 매니폴드와 Itô 동역학 학습하기","authors":"Luke Thompson, Dai Shi, Lequan Lin, Junbin Gao, Andi Han","pos":"#1403","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=k2DxnK87ml","abs":"Neural rough differential equations (NRDEs) learn continuous-time dynamics from irregularly sampled sequences by encoding the input path with signature features, providing robustness to discretisation and sampling irregularity. However, existing NRDEs implicitly rely on algebraic identities that can fail in two important settings: *stochastic dynamics* interpreted in the Itô sense, and *dynamics evolving on manifolds* where curvature renders the effect of repeated derivatives order-dependent. In this work, we propose Branched Neural Rough Differential Equations (B-NRDEs), a unified framework that replaces geometric signature features with tree-based (branched) rough-path lifts, yielding models that remain well-defined under Itô noise and on manifolds. Building on these branched lifts, an Itô-consistent training objective is introduced via the branched signature kernel. We provide an efficient, autodifferentiable package *Stochastax* for computing branched (log-)signatures and solving (manifold) RDEs. Across various applications, including rough Bergomi volatility modelling, sim-to-real $\\mathrm{SO}(3)$ dynamics forecasting, and SPD covariance dynamics, B-NRDE shows consistently strong results.","absKo":"Neural rough differential equations(NRDEs)는 입력 path를 signature feature로 인코딩하여 불규칙하게 샘플링된 sequence로부터 continuous-time dynamics를 학습하며, discretisation과 sampling irregularity에 대한 강건성을 제공한다. 그러나 기존 NRDE는 두 가지 중요한 설정에서 실패할 수 있는 대수적 항등식에 암묵적으로 의존한다. 하나는 Itô 의미로 해석되는 *stochastic dynamics*이고, 다른 하나는 곡률 때문에 반복 미분의 효과가 차수에 의존하게 되는 *manifold 상의 dynamics*이다. 본 연구에서는 geometric signature feature를 tree-based(branched) rough-path lift로 대체하는 통합 프레임워크인 Branched Neural Rough Differential Equations(B-NRDEs)를 제안하며, 이를 통해 Itô noise 아래와 manifold 위에서도 잘 정의되는 model을 얻는다. 이러한 branched lift를 바탕으로, branched signature kernel을 통해 Itô-consistent training objective를 도입한다. 또한 branched (log-)signature 계산과 (manifold) RDE 해법을 위한 효율적이고 autodifferentiable한 패키지 *Stochastax*를 제공한다. rough Bergomi volatility modeling, sim-to-real $\\\\mathrm{SO}(3)$ dynamics forecasting, SPD covariance dynamics를 포함한 다양한 응용 전반에서 B-NRDE는 일관되게 강력한 결과를 보인다."},{"id":"63671","en":"MIMOMamba: From Scalar Duality to Matrix-Valued Attention","ko":"MIMOMamba: 스칼라 이중성에서 행렬값 attention으로","authors":"Yanbo Li, Richard Cornelius Suwandi, Feng Yin, Yiyong SUN, Wei Huang, Wenqiang Pu","pos":"#1404","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=UmQ07sj13y","abs":"<p>The state space duality (SSD) framework, central to modern state-space models (SSMs) such as Mamba, has established an efficient attention-like mechanism by leveraging the commutative property of linear recurrences. However, existing formulations are limited to single-input single-output (SISO) systems that enforce commutativity with a restrictive scalar-identity constraint, which prevents cross-dimensional interactions within the state dynamics. In this work, we generalize SSD to the multi-input multi-output (MIMO) setting by introducing a matrix polynomial parameterization.  This approach not only provides a principled way to ensure commutativity for generalized duality but also induces a shared algebraic structure across state transitions, thereby significantly reducing parameter redundancy. Building on this foundation, we present \\textbf{MIMOMamba}, a multi-head SSM architecture that captures rich cross-dimensional dynamics while retaining linear-time training.  Empirical results on a sequence modeling benchmark show that MIMOMamba matches or exceeds the performance of standard Transformers with only approximately one-third the parameters of the baseline.</p>","absKo":"<p>Mamba와 같은 현대 state-space model(SSM)의 핵심인 state space duality(SSD) framework는 linear recurrence의 교환법칙(commutative property)을 활용하여 효율적인 attention 유사 메커니즘을 확립했다. 그러나 기존 formulation은 state dynamics 내의 cross-dimensional interaction을 방해하는 제한적인 scalar-identity constraint로 commutativity를 강제하는 single-input single-output(SISO) system에만 국한된다. 본 연구에서는 matrix polynomial parameterization을 도입하여 SSD를 multi-input multi-output(MIMO) 설정으로 일반화한다. 이 접근법은 일반화된 duality에서 commutativity를 보장하는 원칙적인 방법을 제공할 뿐만 아니라, state transition 전반에 걸쳐 shared algebraic structure를 유도하여 parameter redundancy를 크게 줄인다. 이 기반 위에서 우리는 linear-time training을 유지하면서도 풍부한 cross-dimensional dynamics를 포착하는 multi-head SSM architecture인 \\textbf{MIMOMamba}를 제시한다. sequence modeling benchmark에서의 실험 결과, MIMOMamba는 baseline의 약 3분의 1에 해당하는 parameter만으로 standard Transformer와 동등하거나 그 이상의 성능을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"66090","en":"One Step Forward and K Steps Back: Better Reasoning with Denoising Recursion Models","ko":"한 걸음 전진, K걸음 후퇴: 디노이징 재귀 모델을 통한 더 나은 추론","authors":"Chris Cameron, Wangzheng Wang, Nikita Ivanov, Ashmita Bhattacharyya, Didier Chételat, Yingxue Zhang","pos":"#1405","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=78MQeA1Jyq","abs":"<p>Looped transformers scale computational depth independent of parameter count by repeatedly applying the same layer. However, training these models over long horizons creates significant optimization challenges. Specifically, it is difficult for looped transformers that start from noise to steer towards a potentially complex output without additional supervision. Diffusion models tackle this issue by corrupting data with varying magnitudes of noise and training the model to reverse it in a single step. However, this process misaligns training and testing behaviour. We introduce Denoising Recursion Models, a method that similarly corrupts data with noise but trains the model to reverse the corruption over multiple recursive steps. This strategy provides a tractable curriculum of intermediate states, while better aligning training with testing and incentivizing non-greedy, forward-looking generation. Through extensive experiments, we showed this approach outperformed the Tiny Recursion Model (TRM) on ARC-AGI, where it recently achieved breakthrough performance.</p>"},{"id":"64412","en":"ParalESN: Enabling parallel information processing in Reservoir Computing","ko":"ParalESN: Reservoir Computing에서 병렬 정보 처리 가능화","authors":"Matteo Pinna, Giacomo Lagomarsini, Andrea Ceni, Claudio Gallicchio","pos":"#1406","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=NsJUKcONFR","abs":"<p>Reservoir Computing (RC) has established itself as an efficient paradigm for temporal processing. However, its scalability remains severely constrained by (i) the necessity of processing temporal data sequentially and (ii) the prohibitive memory footprint of high-dimensional reservoirs. In this work, we revisit RC through the lens of structured operators and state space modeling to address these limitations, introducing Parallel Echo State Network (ParalESN). ParalESN enables the construction of high-dimensional and efficient reservoirs based on diagonal linear recurrence in the complex space, enabling parallel processing of temporal data. We provide a theoretical analysis demonstrating that ParalESN preserves the Echo State Property and the universality guarantees of traditional Echo State Networks while admitting an equivalent representation of arbitrary linear reservoirs in the complex diagonal form. Empirically, ParalESN matches the predictive accuracy of traditional RC on time series benchmarks, while delivering substantial computational savings. On 1-D pixel-level classification tasks, ParalESN achieves competitive accuracy with fully trainable neural networks while reducing computational costs and energy consumption by orders of magnitude. Overall, ParalESN offers a promising, scalable, and principled pathway for integrating RC within the deep learning landscape.</p>","absKo":"<p>Reservoir Computing(RC)은 시계열 처리를 위한 효율적인 패러다임으로 자리 잡았다. 그러나 그 확장성은 여전히 (i) temporal data를 순차적으로 처리해야 한다는 필요성과 (ii) 고차원 reservoir의 과도한 메모리 사용량이라는 두 가지 요인에 의해 심각하게 제약된다. 본 연구에서는 이러한 한계를 해결하기 위해 structured operator와 state space modeling의 관점에서 RC를 재검토하고, Parallel Echo State Network(ParalESN)를 제안한다. ParalESN은 complex space에서의 diagonal linear recurrence를 기반으로 고차원이고 효율적인 reservoir를 구성할 수 있게 하며, temporal data의 병렬 처리를 가능하게 한다. 우리는 ParalESN이 Echo State Property와 기존 Echo State Network의 보편성(universality) 보장을 보존하면서도, 임의의 선형 reservoir를 complex diagonal form으로 동등하게 표현할 수 있음을 보이는 이론적 분석을 제시한다. 실증적으로는, ParalESN이 시계열 벤치마크에서 전통적 RC의 예측 정확도를 맞추면서도 상당한 계산 절감을 제공한다. 1-D pixel-level classification 작업에서는, ParalESN이 완전 학습형 neural network에 견줄 만한 정확도를 달성하는 동시에 계산 비용과 에너지 소비를 여러 자릿수(order of magnitude) 줄인다. 전반적으로 ParalESN은 deep learning 환경에 RC를 통합하기 위한 유망하고 확장 가능하며 원칙적인 경로를 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"61351","en":"Parametric Prior Mapping Framework for Non-stationary Probabilistic Time Series Forecasting","ko":"비정상 확률적 시계열 예측을 위한 Parametric Prior Mapping Framework","authors":"Jinglin Li, Jun Tan, QI Fang, Ning Gui","pos":"#1407","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=r4GbYGbWM5","abs":"<p>Effectively modeling non-stationary dynamics in probabilistic multivariate time series(MTS) forecasting requires balancing expressiveness with robustness. Existing parametric approaches benefit from strong inductive biases but lack flexibility, whereas deep generative models struggle to capture complex temporal dependencies without extensive data and compute. We introduce Parametric Prior Mapping (PPM), a framework that injects parametric structural priors into a generative modeling process. Specifically, PPM utilizes a parametric estimator to derive a dynamic, adaptive prior, which guides the learning of a complex predictive distribution via a learnable mapping. This design allows the model to retain the efficiency of parametric methods while exploiting the expressive power of generative models. Trained with a hybrid objective, PPM yields precise forecasts with well-calibrated uncertainty estimates. Empirical results show that PPM outperforms existing baselines in handling non-stationary data, offering a superior trade-off between accuracy and computational efficiency.</p>","absKo":"<p>확률적 다변량 시계열(MTS) 예측에서 비정상 동역학을 효과적으로 모델링하려면 표현력과 강건성 사이의 균형이 필요하다. 기존의 parametric 접근법은 강한 inductive bias의 이점을 가지지만 유연성이 부족하고, 반면 deep generative model은 충분한 데이터와 연산 자원 없이 복잡한 시간적 의존성을 포착하는 데 어려움을 겪는다. 우리는 parametric structural prior를 generative modeling 과정에 주입하는 프레임워크인 Parametric Prior Mapping (PPM)을 제안한다. 구체적으로, PPM은 parametric estimator를 사용해 동적이고 적응적인 prior를 도출하고, 이를 learnable mapping을 통해 복잡한 predictive distribution의 학습을 안내한다. 이러한 설계는 모델이 parametric method의 효율성을 유지하면서도 generative model의 표현력을 활용할 수 있게 한다. hybrid objective로 학습된 PPM은 정밀한 예측과 잘 보정된 uncertainty estimate를 제공한다. 실험 결과, PPM은 비정상 데이터 처리에서 기존 baseline을 능가하며, 정확도와 계산 효율성 사이에서 더 우수한 trade-off를 제공함을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"64363","en":"Time-series forecasting through the lens of dynamics","ko":"동역학의 관점에서 본 시계열 예측","authors":"Alexis-Raja Brachet, Pierre-Yves Richard, Céline Hudelot","pos":"#1409","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=OL0Vx2FV1g","abs":"While deep learning is facing an homogenization across modalities led by Transformers, they are still challenged by shallow linear models in the time-series forecasting task. Our hypothesis is that models should learn a direct link from past to future data points, which we identify as a learning dynamics capability. We develop an original $\\texttt{PRO-DYN}$ nomenclature to analyze existing models through the lens of dynamics. Two observations thus emerge: **1.** under-performing architectures learn dynamics at most partially, **2.** the location of the dynamics block at the model end is of prime importance. Our systemic and empirical studies both confirm our observations on a set of performance-varying models with diverse backbones. We propose a simple plug-and-play methodology guiding model designs and improvements.","absKo":"딥러닝이 Transformer에 의해 modality 전반에서 점차 획일화되고 있지만, time-series forecasting task에서는 여전히 shallow linear model에 도전받고 있습니다. 우리의 가설은 model이 과거 데이터 포인트에서 미래 데이터 포인트로의 직접적인 연결을 학습해야 하며, 이를 learning dynamics capability로 규정한다는 것입니다. 우리는 dynamics 관점에서 기존 model을 분석하기 위해 원래의 $\\texttt{PRO-DYN}$ 명명법을 개발합니다. 이에 따라 두 가지 관찰이 도출됩니다. **1.** 성능이 낮은 architecture는 dynamics를 많아야 부분적으로만 학습하며, **2.** model 끝단에 dynamics block이 위치하는 것이 매우 중요합니다. 우리의 체계적 및 실증적 연구는 모두 다양한 backbone을 가진 여러 performance-varying model 집합에서 이러한 관찰을 확인합니다. 우리는 model 설계와 개선을 안내하는 간단한 plug-and-play 방법론을 제안합니다."},{"id":"64216","en":"Tri-Scale Neural ODEs for Continuous Multi-Omics Disease Modeling","ko":"연속 다중 오믹스 질병 모델링을 위한 삼중 스케일 Neural ODE","authors":"Shohaib Shaffiey, Massimiliano Pierobon","pos":"#1410","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=PsjSZaunzO","abs":"The fields of AI-based disease fingerprinting, drug discovery and repurposing are currently among the emerging frontiers of machine learning applied to medicine. One major challenge is to obtain robust $\\textit{in-silico}$ modeling of disease progression while accounting for the vastly different time scales of biochemical interactions, from gene expression to protein abundance and metabolic flux. Discrete sequence models inadequately represent such multi-scale interactions, and standard Neural Ordinary Differential Equations (NODEs) often fail to train stably under stiffness (different time scales). To address this, in this paper a Tri-Scale Stiff NODE is introduced, defined by hierarchically coupled latent differential equations that model the causal flow from genes to proteins and metabolites, and optimized using reconstruction error and information-theoretic mutual information. This enables continuous-time modeling of cellular responses to identify not only disease dynamics, but also drug perturbations that act within narrow time windows, often invisible to discrete-time approaches. Lyapunov analysis provides a theoretical guarantee that the modeled trajectories remain stable and well-behaved even under extreme stiffness. The developed modeling methodology is tested upon a public dataset (STATegra B-cell differentiation) and utilized for a proof-of-concept drug repurposing pipeline.","absKo":"AI 기반 질병 fingerprinting, 약물 discovery 및 repurposing 분야는 현재 의학에 머신러닝을 적용하는 emerging frontier 중 하나이다. 핵심 과제 중 하나는 gene expression에서 protein abundance, metabolic flux에 이르기까지 생화학적 상호작용의 시간 스케일이 크게 다른 점을 고려하면서 질병 진행을 견고하게 $\\textit{in-silico}$로 모델링하는 것이다. Discrete sequence model은 이러한 multi-scale interaction을 충분히 표현하지 못하며, 표준 Neural Ordinary Differential Equations (NODEs)는 stiffness(서로 다른 시간 스케일) 하에서 안정적으로 학습되지 못하는 경우가 많다. 이를 해결하기 위해 본 논문에서는 gene에서 protein 및 metabolite로 이어지는 causal flow를 모델링하는 계층적으로 결합된 latent differential equation으로 정의되는 Tri-Scale Stiff NODE를 도입하고, reconstruction error와 information-theoretic mutual information을 사용해 최적화한다. 이를 통해 세포 반응을 continuous-time으로 모델링하여 disease dynamics뿐 아니라 discrete-time 접근법에서는 종종 보이지 않는 좁은 시간 창에서 작동하는 drug perturbation도 식별할 수 있다. Lyapunov analysis는 극심한 stiffness 하에서도 모델링된 trajectory가 안정적이고 well-behaved하게 유지된다는 이론적 보장을 제공한다. 개발된 modeling methodology는 public dataset(STATegra B-cell differentiation)에서 테스트되었고, proof-of-concept drug repurposing pipeline에 활용되었다."},{"id":"65941","en":"WaveSSM: Multiscale State-Space Models for Non-stationary Signal Attention","ko":"WaveSSM: 비정상 신호 Attention을 위한 다중 스케일 State-Space 모델","authors":"Ruben Solozabal, Alejandro Solozabal, Hilal AlQuabeh, Klea Ziu, Kentaro Inui, Martin Takac","pos":"#1411","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=8f5JVzcFvA","abs":"<p>State-space models (SSMs) have emerged as a powerful foundation for long-range sequence modeling, with the HiPPO framework showing that continuous-time projection operators can be used to derive stable, memory-efficient dynamical systems that encode the past history of the input signal. However, existing projection-based SSMs often rely on polynomial bases with global temporal support, whose inductive biases are poorly matched to signals exhibiting localized or transient structure. In this work, we introduce \\emph{WaveSSM}, a collection of SSMs constructed over wavelet frames. Our key observation is that wavelet frames yield a localized support on the temporal dimension, useful for tasks requiring precise localization. Empirically, we show that on equal conditions, \\textit{WaveSSM} outperforms orthogonal counterparts as S4 on real-world datasets with transient dynamics, including physiological signals on the PTB-XL dataset and raw audio on Speech Commands.</p>"},{"id":"64284","en":"Dywave: Event-Aligned Dynamic Tokenization for Heterogeneous IoT Sensing Signals","ko":"Dywave: 이기종 IoT 센싱 신호를 위한 이벤트 정렬 동적 토큰화","authors":"Tomoyoshi Kimura, Denizhan Kara, Jinyang Li, Hongjue Zhao, Yigong Hu, Yizhuo Chen, Xiaomin OUYANG, Shengzhong Liu, Tarek Abdelzaher","pos":"#1500","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=P9FgQGxHCW","abs":"<p>Internet of Things (IoT) systems continuously collect heterogeneous sensing signals from ubiquitous sensors to support intelligent applications such as human activity analysis, emotion monitoring, and environmental perception. These signals are inherently non-stationary and multi-scale, posing unique challenges for standard tokenization techniques.  This paper proposes Dywave, a dynamic tokenization framework for IoT sensing signals that constructs compact input representations aligned with intrinsic temporal structures and underlying physical events. Dywave leverages wavelet-based hierarchical decomposition, identifies meaningful temporal boundaries corresponding to underlying semantic events, and adaptively compresses redundant intervals while preserving temporal coherence. Extensive evaluations on five real-world IoT sensing datasets across activity recognition, stress assessment, and nearby object detection demonstrate that Dywave outperforms state-of-the-art methods by up to 12\\% in accuracy, while improving computational efficiency by reducing input token lengths by up to 75\\% across mainstream sequence models. Moreover, Dywave exhibits improved robustness to domain shifts and varying sequence lengths.</p>","absKo":"<p>Internet of Things (IoT) system은 인간 활동 분석, 감정 모니터링, 환경 인식과 같은 지능형 application을 지원하기 위해 ubiquitous sensor로부터 이질적인 sensing signal을 지속적으로 수집한다. 이러한 signal은 본질적으로 non-stationary하고 multi-scale이어서, 표준 tokenization technique에 고유한 도전을 제기한다. 이 논문은 IoT sensing signal을 위한 dynamic tokenization framework인 Dywave를 제안하며, 이는 내재적 temporal structure와 underlying physical event에 정렬된 compact input representation을 구성한다. Dywave는 wavelet 기반 hierarchical decomposition을 활용하고, underlying semantic event에 대응하는 의미 있는 temporal boundary를 식별하며, temporal coherence를 유지하면서 redundant interval을 적응적으로 압축한다. activity recognition, stress assessment, nearby object detection 전반에 걸친 다섯 개의 real-world IoT sensing dataset에 대한 광범위한 평가에서 Dywave는 state-of-the-art method 대비 정확도를 최대 12\\%까지 향상시키는 동시에, 주류 sequence model 전반에서 input token length를 최대 75\\%까지 줄여 computational efficiency를 개선함을 보인다. 더 나아가 Dywave는 domain shift와 다양한 sequence length에 대해서도 향상된 robustness를 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"64661","en":"Dynamic Fractal Mamba: A Neural Renormalization Group Flow for Scale-Invariant Sequence Modeling","ko":"Dynamic Fractal Mamba: Scale-Invariant Sequence Modeling을 위한 Neural Renormalization Group Flow","authors":"Shenglei Fang, Xianfang Sun, You Zhou","pos":"#1501","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=L8a9GRfoly","abs":"<p>Sequence models typically operate at a fixed temporal or spatial scale and struggle to generalize to substantially longer horizons or higher resolutions without retraining. Existing hierarchical architectures expand receptive fields but rely on scale-specific parameters and lack mechanisms to enforce consistent dynamics across scales. We propose \\textbf{Dynamic Fractal Mamba (DF-Mamba)}, a recursive state-space model that applies a single shared operator across multiple scales. By sharing parameters across recursion depths and exponentially scaling the effective time step, DF-Mamba achieves an exponentially expanding receptive field while preserving linear computational complexity. A learned content-aware coarse-graining module aggregates representations across scales. Auxiliary reconstruction and cross-scale consistency objectives stabilize recursive training. We evaluate DF-Mamba on long-range time-series forecasting, spatial transcriptomics, and computational pathology. Across all tasks, DF-Mamba consistently outperforms Transformers and flat Mamba baselines while using fewer parameters and maintaining linear-time scalability. Importantly, models trained on short sequences or low-resolution inputs generalize in a zero-shot manner to substantially larger temporal and spatial scales unseen during training. These results demonstrate that recursive parameter sharing provides an effective inductive bias for learning scale-consistent and efficient sequence representations.</p>","absKo":"<p>Sequence models는 일반적으로 고정된 temporal 또는 spatial scale에서 동작하며, 재학습 없이 훨씬 더 긴 horizon이나 더 높은 resolution으로 일반화하는 데 어려움을 겪는다. 기존 hierarchical architectures는 receptive field를 확장하지만 scale-specific parameters에 의존하며, scale 전반에 걸쳐 일관된 dynamics를 강제할 메커니즘이 부족하다. 우리는 여러 scale에 걸쳐 하나의 공유 operator를 적용하는 recursive state-space model인 \\textbf{Dynamic Fractal Mamba (DF-Mamba)}를 제안한다. recursion depth 전반에 걸쳐 parameter를 공유하고 effective time step을 지수적으로 스케일링함으로써, DF-Mamba는 linear computational complexity를 유지하면서 receptive field를 지수적으로 확장한다. 학습된 content-aware coarse-graining module은 scale 간 representation을 집계한다. auxiliary reconstruction 및 cross-scale consistency objective는 recursive training을 안정화한다. 우리는 long-range time-series forecasting, spatial transcriptomics, computational pathology에서 DF-Mamba를 평가한다. 모든 task에서 DF-Mamba는 Transformer와 flat Mamba baseline을 일관되게 능가하면서도 더 적은 parameter를 사용하고 linear-time scalability를 유지한다. 특히 short sequence나 low-resolution input으로 학습된 model은 training 동안 보지 못한 훨씬 더 큰 temporal 및 spatial scale로 zero-shot generalization을 보인다. 이러한 결과는 recursive parameter sharing이 scale-consistent하고 효율적인 sequence representation을 학습하기 위한 효과적인 inductive bias임을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"66198","en":"Delving into Non-Exchangeability for Conformal Prediction in Graph-Structured Multivariate Time Series","ko":"그래프 구조 다변량 시계열에서 Conformal Prediction을 위한 비교환성 고찰","authors":"Ruichao Guo, Xingyao Han, Wenshui Luo, Zhe Liu, Chen Gong, Hesheng Wang","pos":"#1502","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=5s5zlewQRI","abs":"<p>Point forecasting for graph-structured multivariate time series is a fundamental problem, but rigorous uncertainty quantification for such predictions is still underexplored. Conformal prediction (CP) offers uncertainty estimation with a solid coverage guarantee under the exchangeability assumption, which requires the joint data distribution to be unchanged under permutation. However, in graph-structured time series, inherent cross-node coupling can violate the exchangeability condition, making direct application of CP unreliable.  Inspired by the spectral graph theory, such coupling resides in global trends and can be characterized by the low-frequency components, while high-frequency components are nearly exchangeable. Therefore, we propose a novel concept named <strong>S</strong>pectral <strong>G</strong>raph <strong>C</strong>onditional <strong>E</strong>xchangeability (SGCE), which conditions exchangeable high-frequency components on low-frequency ones to preserve global trends and enable effective CP in the spectral domain. Based on SGCE, we further propose <strong>S</strong>pectral <strong>C</strong>onformal prediction via w<strong>A</strong>ve<strong>LE</strong>t transform (SCALE). SCALE uses graph wavelets to decompose low/high-frequency components and conformalizes high-frequency residuals via adaptive gating over a low-frequency embedding. Experimental results on real-world traffic datasets show that SCALE not only achieves valid coverage but also consistently improves the coverage-efficiency trade-off over the state-of-the-art CP methods.</p>"},{"id":"64957","en":"DITING: A Weak Degradation Listener for Battery Lifetime Early Prediction","ko":"DITING: 배터리 수명 조기 예측을 위한 Weak Degradation Listener","authors":"Hao Miao, Ni Zhang, Zefei Ning, Li Wang","pos":"#1503","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=IMH7K8Jn6A","abs":"<p>Battery lifetime early prediction is crucial for safety assessment and decision planning. However, early-stage degradation signals are extremely weak and difficult to distinguish from noise. Existing methods primarily rely on denoising or signal decomposition, which risks losing critical degradation cues. In nature, most organisms exhibit binaural effect, exploiting differences between left and right auditory inputs to enhance perceptual reliability. Inspired by this, we propose DITING, a weak degradation listener for battery lifetime early prediction. DITING first employs optimal-transport-based selective matching to extract a robust health template from initial cycles for degradation representation. To manifest degradation signals from noise, we further design a tri-coupled degradation manifestation mechanism. By exploiting the randomness of noise, matched responses under symmetric coupling suppress stochastic fluctuations. Conversely, cumulative deviations driven by degradation propagate through the coupling to form stable bilateral discrepancies. This design effectively amplifies weak cues in the early stage for lifetime prediction. Experiments on multiple datasets demonstrate that DITING achieves state-of-the-art performance and provides more reliable early support for full-lifecycle battery management. The code is available at  https://anonymous.4open.science/r/Batt_DITING.</p>"},{"id":"66194","en":"KineFlow: Kinematic Second-Order Flow Matching for Time-Series Forecasting","ko":"KineFlow: 시계열 예측을 위한 운동학적 2차 Flow Matching","authors":"Haiqi Jiang, Hui Xiong","pos":"#200","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=5uxdusZsa7","abs":"<p>Conventional time-series discriminative forecasting relies on point-wise regression, which inherently induces over-smoothing and fails to capture stochastic volatility in complex systems. While first-order generative flow matching methods mitigate this issue, they ignore system inertia, resulting in phase-space ambiguities and high sensitivity to noise. We introduce KineFlow, a generative time-series forecasting framework that augments flow matching with a phase-space Neural Acceleration Field, treating exogenous inputs as driving forces that produce gradual momentum shifts rather than abrupt state perturbations. This second-order formulation serves as a structural filter via double integration, suppressing high-frequency noise and producing robust, physically consistent predictions. Extensive experiments on six real-world benchmarks demonstrate that KineFlow achieves an average 15% MSE improvement over discriminative baselines and an 8% gain in CRPS compared to state-of-the-art generative methods.</p>"},{"id":"61786","en":"MN-Diff: Diffusion Parameterized  MoE-NCDE for Continuous Time Series Generation with Irregular Observations","ko":"MN-Diff: 불규칙 관측이 있는 연속 시계열 생성을 위한 Diffusion Parameterized MoE-NCDE","authors":"Xu Zhang, Junwei Deng, Chang Xu, Hao Li, Jiang Bian","pos":"#201","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=mx8nvMUfxL","abs":"<p>Time series generation (TSG) is widely used across domains, yet most existing methods assume regular sampling and fixed output resolutions. These assumptions are often violated in practice, where observations are irregular and sparse, while downstream applications require continuous and high-resolution TS. Although Neural Controlled Differential Equation (NCDE) is promising for modeling irregular TS, it is constrained by a single dynamics function, tightly coupled optimization, and limited ability to adapt learned dynamics to newly generated samples from the generative model. We propose MN-Diff, a continuous TSG framework that enhances NCDE with a Mixture-of-Experts (MoE) dynamics function and a decoupled architectural design for dynamics-focused training. To further enable NCDE to generalize to newly generated samples, MN-Diff employs a diffusion model to parameterize the NCDE temporal dynamics parameters (MoE weights), i.e., jointly learn the distribution of TS data and MoE weights. This design allows sample-specific NCDE parameters to be generated for continuous TS generation. Experiments on ten public and synthetic datasets demonstrate that MN-Diff consistently outperforms strong baselines on both irregular-to-regular and irregular-to-continuous TSG tasks. The code is available at the link https://anonymous.4open.science/r/MN-Diff-2688.</p>","absKo":"<p>Time series generation(TSG)은 여러 도메인에서 널리 사용되지만, 기존 방법의 대부분은 규칙적인 sampling과 고정된 output resolution을 가정한다. 이러한 가정은 실제 환경에서 종종 깨지는데, 관측은 불규칙하고 희소한 반면 downstream application은 continuous하고 high-resolution TS를 요구하기 때문이다. Neural Controlled Differential Equation(NCDE)은 불규칙한 TS를 모델링하는 데 유망하지만, 단일 dynamics function, 강하게 결합된 optimization, 그리고 generative model에서 새로 생성된 sample에 학습된 dynamics를 적응시키는 제한된 능력에 의해 제약된다. 우리는 MN-Diff를 제안한다. 이는 MoE(Mixture-of-Experts) dynamics function과 dynamics 중심 학습을 위한 분리된 architectural design으로 NCDE를 강화한 continuous TSG framework이다. NCDE가 새로 생성된 sample에 대해 더 잘 일반화하도록 하기 위해, MN-Diff는 diffusion model을 사용하여 NCDE temporal dynamics parameter(MoE weight)를 parameterize한다. 즉, TS data 분포와 MoE weight의 분포를 jointly learn한다. 이 설계는 sample-specific NCDE parameter를 생성하여 continuous TS generation을 수행할 수 있게 한다. 10개의 공개 및 synthetic dataset에서의 실험은 MN-Diff가 불규칙-규칙(irregular-to-regular) 및 불규칙-연속(irregular-to-continuous) TSG task 모두에서 강력한 baseline을 일관되게 능가함을 보여준다. 코드는 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/MN-Diff-2688 에서 제공된다.</p>"},{"id":"63111","en":"ReAugment: Targeted Few-Shot Time Series Augmentation via Model Zoo-Guided Reinforcement Learning","ko":"ReAugment: 모델 주 유도 강화학습을 통한 표적 소수샷 시계열 증강","authors":"Haochen Yuan, Yutong Wang, Yihong Chen, Yunbo Wang, Xiaokang Yang","pos":"#203","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Zza6vGmNfl","abs":"<p>Few-shot time series forecasting is fundamentally challenged by the scarcity of high-quality training data and the risk of severe overfitting. To address this issue, we propose ReAugment, a reinforcement learning (RL) framework that explicitly learns where and how to augment time series data. ReAugment maintains a zoo of forecasting models and measures prediction diversity across them to identify training samples that are most prone to overfitting. These samples serve as anchor points and are used as inputs to the data augmentation process. We then employ an RL approach to learn transformation policies, using a model zoo-guided reward function to bias the transformed data to overfit-prone regions of the training distribution that are most beneficial for generalization. A key advantage of the RL formulation is that it avoids backpropagating gradients through the forecasting models, thereby mitigating gradient vanishing. Experiments across diverse forecasting architectures demonstrate the effectiveness of ReAugment in both few-shot and standard time series forecasting.</p>","absKo":"<p>Few-shot time series forecasting은 고품질 training data의 부족과 심각한 overfitting 위험이라는 근본적인 문제에 직면한다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 time series data를 어디에, 어떻게 augment할지를 명시적으로 학습하는 reinforcement learning (RL) framework인 ReAugment를 제안한다. ReAugment는 forecasting model zoo를 유지하고, 그들 사이의 prediction diversity를 측정하여 overfitting에 가장 취약한 training sample을 식별한다. 이러한 샘플은 anchor point 역할을 하며 data augmentation process의 입력으로 사용된다. 이후 우리는 RL 접근법을 사용하여 transformation policy를 학습하고, model zoo가 안내하는 reward function을 통해 변환된 데이터가 일반화에 가장 유익한, training distribution 내 overfit-prone region으로 편향되도록 한다. RL 정식화의 핵심 장점은 forecasting model을 통해 gradient를 역전파할 필요가 없으므로 gradient vanishing을 완화한다는 점이다. 다양한 forecasting architecture 전반의 실험은 few-shot과 standard time series forecasting 모두에서 ReAugment의 효과를 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"63134","en":"Reviving Error Correction in Modern Deep Time-Series Forecasting","ko":"현대 심층 시계열 예측에서 오차 보정의 부활","authors":"Minh Nguyen, Van Dai Do, Huu Nguyen, Dung Nguyen, Kien Do, Hung Le","pos":"#204","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ZlDndRDMHm","abs":"<p>Modern deep-learning models have achieved remarkable success in time-series forecasting. Yet, their performance degrades in long-term prediction due to error accumulation in autoregressive inference, where predictions are recursively used as inputs. While classical error correction mechanisms (ECMs) have long been used in statistical methods, their applicability to deep learning models remains limited or ineffective. In this work, we revisit the error accumulation problem in deep time-series forecasting and investigate the role and necessity of ECMs in this new context. We propose a simple, architecture-agnostic error correction model that can be integrated with any existing forecaster without requiring retraining. By explicitly decomposing predictions into trend and seasonal components and training the corrector to adjust each separately, we introduce the Universal Error Corrector with Seasonal–Trend Decomposition (UEC-STD), which significantly improves correction accuracy and robustness across 4 backbones and 10 datasets. Our findings provide a practical tool for enhancing forecasts while offering new insights into mitigating autoregressive errors in deep time-series models.</p>","absKo":"<p>현대 deep-learning model은 time-series forecasting에서 놀라운 성공을 거두었다. 그러나 autoregressive inference에서는 예측이 재귀적으로 입력으로 사용되면서 error accumulation이 발생해 장기 예측 성능이 저하된다. 통계적 방법에서는 classical error correction mechanism (ECM)이 오래전부터 사용되어 왔지만, deep learning model에 대한 적용 가능성은 제한적이거나 비효과적이었다. 본 연구에서는 deep time-series forecasting에서의 error accumulation 문제를 재검토하고, 이 새로운 맥락에서 ECM의 역할과 필요성을 살펴본다. 우리는 기존 forecaster와 함께 재학습 없이 통합할 수 있는, 단순하고 architecture-agnostic한 error correction model을 제안한다. 예측을 trend와 seasonal component로 명시적으로 분해하고 corrector가 각 부분을 별도로 조정하도록 학습함으로써, 우리는 Universal Error Corrector with Seasonal–Trend Decomposition (UEC-STD)을 제안하며, 이는 4개의 backbone과 10개의 dataset 전반에서 correction accuracy와 robustness를 크게 향상시킨다. 우리의 결과는 forecast를 강화하기 위한 실용적 도구를 제공함과 동시에, deep time-series model에서 autoregressive error를 완화하는 새로운 통찰을 제시한다.</p>"},{"id":"65231","en":"KITE: Knowledge-Guided Probabilistic Modeling for Time Series Forecasting with Exogenous Variables","ko":"KITE: 외생 변수를 포함한 시계열 예측을 위한 지식 기반 확률 모델링","authors":"Hanyin Cheng, Jingrong Zhou, Yang Shu, Chenjuan Guo","pos":"#300","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=FYkXNAqq2D","abs":"<p>Probabilistic forecasting with exogenous variables is vital for decision-making but remains underexplored compared to deterministic methods. We propose KITE, a knowledge-guided probabilistic modeling framework designed to bridge this gap by addressing two key bottlenecks: (1) topological disparity in sampling initialization and (2) spurious covariate correlations during the iterative conditional generation process. KITE introduces a <em>History-Conditional Manifold</em> to construct an informative source distribution from historical dynamics, effectively anchoring the starting point closer to the target space. Additionally, a <em>Knowledge-Guided Conditioning</em> module is developed to regularize variable interactions using statistical priors, suppressing spurious correlations and enhancing the robustness of covariate conditioning. Extensive experiments demonstrate that KITE outperforms state-of-the-art methods in both deterministic and probabilistic forecasting.</p>"},{"id":"64934","en":"Generative Modeling of Irregular Time Series via SDE-Induced Continuous-Discrete Variational Inference","ko":"SDE-Induced Continuous-Discrete 변분 추론을 통한 불규칙 시계열의 Generative Modeling","authors":"Zexin Yuan, Qinliang Su, Junxi Xiao","pos":"#301","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=IXdjkxDXI0","abs":"<p>Irregular time series arise ubiquitously in real-world systems, where observations are sparse, asynchronous, and governed by underlying continuous-time dynamics. Existing continuous–discrete state-space models typically rely on path-based variational inference, which is computationally expensive or constrained by restrictive posterior assumptions. We propose SDEVI, a novel framework that performs variational inference directly on the joint distribution over discrete-time observations, while guaranteeing consistency with an underlying continuous process governed by a Stochastic Differential Equation(SDE). SDEVI employs a variational posterior induced by linear time-varying SDEs as a scalable inference backbone. To enable intricate dynamics modeling for real-world data, we introduce non-linear-SDE-induced variational inference and generalize our framework to the complex domain. Extensive experiments across healthcare, physics, climate, and IoT benchmarks demonstrate state-of-the-art performance on interpolation, extrapolation, regression, and classification tasks.</p>"},{"id":"66019","en":"DropoutTS: Sample-Adaptive Dropout for Robust Time Series Forecasting","ko":"DropoutTS: 강건한 시계열 예측을 위한 표본 적응형 Dropout","authors":"Siru Zhong, Yiqiu Liu, Zhiqing Cui, Zezhi Shao, Fei Wang, Qingsong Wen, Yuxuan Liang","pos":"#302","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=7sksHLUvhH","abs":"<p>Deep time series models are vulnerable to noisy data ubiquitous in real-world applications. Existing robustness strategies either prune data or rely on costly prior quantification, failing to balance effectiveness and efficiency. In this paper, we introduce DropoutTS, a model-agnostic plugin that shifts the paradigm from \"what\" to learn to \"how much\" to learn. DropoutTS employs a Sample-Adaptive Dropout mechanism: leveraging spectral sparsity to efficiently quantify instance-level noise via reconstruction residuals, it dynamically calibrates model learning capacity by mapping noise to adaptive dropout rates—selectively suppressing spurious fluctuations while preserving fine-grained fidelity. Extensive experiments across diverse noise regimes and open benchmarks show DropoutTS consistently boosts superior backbones’ performance, delivering advanced robustness with negligible parameter overhead and no architectural modifications. Our code is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/DropoutTS/.</p>"},{"id":"66063","en":"Controlled SDEs for Long-Horizon Motion Generation under Latent Decision Uncertainty","ko":"잠재 결정 불확실성 하에서 장기 시야 모션 생성을 위한 제어된 SDE","authors":"Han Zhang, Nenggan Zheng","pos":"#303","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=7NOuDCtuMs","abs":"<p>Long-horizon motion prediction under external commands is challenged by latent decision uncertainty, where the internal states governing future behavior are unobservable and evolve stochastically over time. This issue is particularly pronounced in biological agents, whose motion trajectories reflect decision-making processes rooted in underlying cognitive states. To address these challenges, we propose CogSDE, a formulation of the controlled stochastic differential equation (SDE) for modeling instruction-driven latent decision dynamics. The drift term in the SDE incorporates a dual-channel control modulation mechanism, enabling external commands to modulate the latent state evolution. The diffusion term in the SDE adopts a state-dependent operator to model intrinsic uncertainty in latent decision dynamics. Furthermore, we establish a theoretical upper bound on the long-horizon prediction of CogSDE through dissipativity-based analysis. Experiments demonstrate that CogSDE consistently improves predictive accuracy in long-horizon motion generation. Importantly, predicted trajectories remain well aligned with control instructions over extended horizons, a property widely recognized as challenging in long-horizon motion prediction.</p>"},{"id":"62513","en":"Anti-Aliasing Matters: A Dynamic Network for Time Series Forecasting","ko":"안티-앨리어싱이 중요하다: 시계열 예측을 위한 Dynamic Network","authors":"Heng Zhou, Xin Sun, Chao LI","pos":"#304","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=fvfJWiTrfF","abs":"<p>Real-world time series inherently exhibit complex temporal patterns. Within chaotic systems, significant mixing and entanglement occur between different time-varying modes. Given that time series exhibit distinctly different patterns at various sampling scales, downsampling to extract multiscale features is a common approach. However, conventional downsampling causes high-frequency components in the original signal, those exceeding the new Nyquist frequency, to undergo spectral folding. This erroneously introduces spurious low-frequency patterns, perceived as low-frequency noise, thereby leading to the <em><strong>aliasing problem</strong></em>. To address this problem, we propose a Decomposition-Prevention-Fusion architecture framework called <strong>DMANet</strong>, which introduces the <strong>D</strong>ynamic <strong>M</strong>ultiscale <strong>A</strong>nti-Aliasing <strong>Net</strong>work. Specifically, DMANet comprises two key components: Multiscale Convolutional Downsampling, designed to capture temporal dependencies and inter-channel interactions, and an Anti-Aliasing Operation, which includes Pre-Sampling Anti-Aliasing Filtering and Post-Sampling Interpolation. These designs guarantee the fidelity of multiscale features before and after downsampling. We show that by mitigating the risk of aliasing, our proposed simple convolutional downsampling architecture achieves performance competitive with common baselines. Our codes are available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/DMANet.</p>","absKo":"<p>실세계 time series는 본질적으로 복잡한 temporal pattern을 보인다. chaotic system 내부에서는 서로 다른 시간 변화 mode들 사이에 significant mixing과 entanglement가 발생한다. time series가 서로 다른 sampling scale에서 뚜렷이 다른 pattern을 보인다는 점을 고려할 때, multiscale feature를 추출하기 위한 downsampling은 흔한 접근이다. 그러나 전통적인 downsampling은 원 신호의 high-frequency component 중 새로운 Nyquist frequency를 초과하는 성분이 spectral folding을 겪게 한다. 이로 인해 low-frequency pattern으로 잘못 인식되는 가짜 low-frequency pattern이 유입되며, 결과적으로 <em><strong>aliasing problem</strong></em>이 발생한다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 <strong>DMANet</strong>이라는 Decomposition-Prevention-Fusion architecture framework를 제안하며, 이는 <strong>D</strong>ynamic <strong>M</strong>ultiscale <strong>A</strong>nti-Aliasing <strong>Net</strong>work를 도입한다. 구체적으로 DMANet은 두 가지 핵심 구성 요소로 이루어진다: temporal dependency와 inter-channel interaction을 포착하도록 설계된 Multiscale Convolutional Downsampling, 그리고 Pre-Sampling Anti-Aliasing Filtering과 Post-Sampling Interpolation을 포함하는 Anti-Aliasing Operation이다. 이러한 설계는 downsampling 전후의 multiscale feature fidelity를 보장한다. 우리는 aliasing 위험을 완화함으로써, 제안한 단순 convolutional downsampling architecture가 일반적인 baseline과 경쟁력 있는 성능을 달성함을 보인다. 코드는 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/DMANet 에서 확인할 수 있다.</p>"},{"id":"61825","en":"Efficient Learning of Deep State Space Models via Importance Smoothing","ko":"Importance Smoothing을 통한 Deep State Space Model의 효율적 학습","authors":"John-Joseph Brady, Nikolas Nüsken, Yunpeng Li","pos":"#3515","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=md3glg1Lft","abs":"Latent state space systems are ubiquitous in statistical modelling, arising naturally when a time-series is observed through a noisy measurement function, however training deep state space models (DSSM) at scale remains difficult. Two largely distinct strategies and literatures have developed around the training of DSSMs. Firstly, auto-encoding DSSMs train generative DSSMs by optimising a variational lower bound. Secondly, DSSMs trained by back-propagating the outputs of a classical sequential Monte Carlo algorithm (SMC). Such approaches can train DSSMs for discriminative as well as generative tasks, however, due to the sequentiality of their forward pass, scale poorly on modern hardware. We propose a new training method _Parallel Variational Monte Carlo_ (PVMC) that bridges the gap between the paradigms, and can be used robustly to train DSSMs for both discriminative and generative tasks. Our method achieves state-of-the-art or better results on a set of baseline experiments and trains $10\\times$ faster than the fastest competing SMC approach.","absKo":"Latent state space system은 통계적 모델링에서 매우 흔하며, time-series가 noisy measurement function을 통해 관측될 때 자연스럽게 나타난다. 그러나 대규모로 deep state space model (DSSM)을 학습하는 일은 여전히 어렵다. DSSM 학습을 둘러싸고 크게 구분되는 두 가지 전략과 연구 흐름이 발전해 왔다. 첫째, auto-encoding DSSM은 variational lower bound를 최적화하여 generative DSSM을 학습한다. 둘째, classical sequential Monte Carlo algorithm (SMC)의 출력을 back-propagation하는 방식으로 학습된 DSSM이 있다. 이러한 접근법은 discriminative task와 generative task 모두에 대해 DSSM을 학습할 수 있지만, forward pass가 sequential하다는 특성 때문에 현대 하드웨어에서는 확장성이 떨어진다. 우리는 두 paradigm 사이의 간극을 메우고, discriminative task와 generative task 모두에 대해 DSSM을 견고하게 학습할 수 있는 새로운 training method인 _Parallel Variational Monte Carlo_ (PVMC)를 제안한다. 우리의 방법은 기준 실험 집합에서 state-of-the-art와 같거나 더 나은 결과를 달성했으며, 가장 빠른 경쟁 SMC 접근법보다 10배 빠르게 학습된다."},{"id":"62603","en":"Neural Modular Physics for Elastic Simulation","ko":"탄성 시뮬레이션을 위한 Neural Modular Physics","authors":"Yifei Li, Haixu Wu, Zeyi Xu, Tuur Stuyck, Wojciech Matusik","pos":"#3612","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=f7PUjzI60h","abs":"<p>Learning-based methods have made significant progress in physics simulation, typically approximating dynamics with a monolithic end-to-end optimized neural network. Although these models offer an effective way to simulation, they may lose essential features compared to traditional numerical simulators, such as physical interpretability and reliability. Drawing inspiration from classical simulators that operate in a modular fashion, this paper presents Neural Modular Physics (NMP) for elastic simulation, which combines the approximation capacity of neural networks with the physical reliability of traditional simulators. Beyond the previous monolithic learning paradigm, NMP enables direct supervision of intermediate quantities and physical constraints by decomposing elastic dynamics into physically meaningful neural modules connected through intermediate physical quantities. With a specialized architecture and training strategy, our method transforms the numerical computation flow into a modular neural simulator, achieving improved physical consistency and generalizability. Experimentally, NMP demonstrates superior generalization to unseen initial conditions and resolutions, stable long-horizon simulation, better preservation of physical properties compared to other neural simulators, and greater feasibility in scenarios with unknown underlying dynamics than traditional simulators.</p>","absKo":"<p>학습 기반 방법들은 물리 시뮬레이션에서 상당한 진전을 이루었으며, 보통 동역학을 단일한 end-to-end 최적화 신경망으로 근사한다. 이러한 모델은 시뮬레이션을 위한 효과적인 방법을 제공하지만, 물리적 해석 가능성과 신뢰성과 같은 전통적인 수치 시뮬레이터의 핵심 특성을 잃을 수 있다. 모듈식 방식으로 동작하는 고전적 시뮬레이터에서 영감을 받아, 본 논문은 탄성 시뮬레이션을 위한 Neural Modular Physics (NMP)를 제시하며, 이는 신경망의 근사 능력과 전통적 시뮬레이터의 물리적 신뢰성을 결합한다. 이전의 단일체 학습 패러다임을 넘어, NMP는 탄성 동역학을 물리적으로 의미 있는 신경 모듈들로 분해하고 이들을 중간 물리량을 통해 연결함으로써 중간량과 물리 제약에 대한 직접적인 supervision을 가능하게 한다. 특화된 아키텍처와 학습 전략을 통해, 우리의 방법은 수치 계산 흐름을 모듈형 신경 시뮬레이터로 전환하여 물리적 일관성과 일반화 성능을 향상시킨다. 실험적으로 NMP는 보지 못한 초기 조건과 해상도에 대한 우수한 일반화, 안정적인 장기 시뮬레이션, 다른 신경 시뮬레이터 대비 더 나은 물리적 성질 보존, 그리고 전통적 시뮬레이터보다 미지의 underlying dynamics가 존재하는 상황에서의 더 큰 적용 가능성을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"61675","en":"SEER: Transformer-based Robust Time Series Forecasting via Automated Patch Enhancement and Replacement","ko":"SEER: 자동 Patch Enhancement와 Replacement를 통한 Transformer 기반 강건한 시계열 예측","authors":"Xiangfei Qiu, Xvyuan Liu, Tianen Shen, Xingjian Wu, Hanyin Cheng, Bin Yang, Jilin Hu","pos":"#205","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=nqnlfxuN8x","abs":"Time series forecasting is important in many fields that require accurate predictions for decision-making. Patching techniques, commonly used and effective in time series modeling, help capture temporal dependencies by dividing the data into patches. However, existing patch-based methods fail to dynamically select patches and typically use all patches during the prediction process. In real-world time series, there are often low-quality issues during data collection, such as missing values, distribution shifts, anomalies and white noise, which may cause some patches to contain low-quality information, negatively impacting the prediction results. To address this issue, this study proposes a robust time series forecasting framework called $\\textbf{SEER}$. Firstly, we propose an $\\textit{Augmented Embedding Module}$, which improves patch-wise representations using a Mixture-of-Experts~(MoE) architecture and obtains series-wise token representations through a channel-adaptive perception mechanism. Secondly, we introduce a $\\textit{Learnable Patch Replacement Module}$, which enhances forecasting robustness and model accuracy through a two-stage process: 1) a dynamic filtering mechanism eliminates negative patch-wise tokens; 2) a replaced attention module substitutes the identified low-quality patches with global series-wise token, further refining their representations through a causal attention mechanism. Comprehensive experimental results demonstrate the SOTA performance of SEER.","absKo":"시계열 예측은 의사결정을 위한 정확한 예측이 필요한 많은 분야에서 중요하다. 시계열 모델링에서 널리 사용되고 효과적인 patching 기법은 데이터를 patch로 나눔으로써 temporal dependency를 포착하는 데 도움을 준다. 그러나 기존 patch-based 방법은 patch를 동적으로 선택하지 못하며, 예측 과정에서 일반적으로 모든 patch를 사용한다. 실제 시계열에서는 데이터 수집 과정에서 missing value, distribution shift, anomaly, white noise와 같은 저품질 문제가 자주 발생하며, 이로 인해 일부 patch에 저품질 정보가 포함되어 예측 결과에 부정적 영향을 줄 수 있다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해, 본 연구는 $\\textbf{SEER}$라는 강건한 시계열 예측 framework를 제안한다. 첫째, 우리는 $\\textit{Augmented Embedding Module}$을 제안한다. 이 모듈은 Mixture-of-Experts~(MoE) architecture를 사용하여 patch-wise representation을 개선하고, channel-adaptive perception mechanism을 통해 series-wise token representation을 획득한다. 둘째, 우리는 $\\textit{Learnable Patch Replacement Module}$을 도입한다. 이 모듈은 두 단계 과정으로 예측 강건성과 model 정확도를 향상시킨다. 1) dynamic filtering mechanism이 부정적인 patch-wise token을 제거하고, 2) replaced attention module이 식별된 저품질 patch를 global series-wise token으로 대체한 뒤, causal attention mechanism을 통해 그 표현을 추가로 정교화한다. 포괄적인 실험 결과는 SEER의 SOTA 성능을 보여준다."},{"id":"61402","en":"When less gives more: bias from small dataset can speed up training","ko":"적을수록 더 많아질 때: 작은 데이터셋의 Bias가 학습을 가속할 수 있다","authors":"Jingwen Liu, Ezra Edelman, Surbhi Goel, Bingbin Liu","pos":"#1300","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=qcb833SRNd","abs":"<p>As data scaling approaches its natural limits, recent work has explored the potential of data reuse, whose impact on optimization remains poorly understood. This work investigates how data repetition affects learning efficiency in terms of compute. We investigate an inverse-scaling effect that using less data can lead to faster convergence, which is observed across algorithmic tasks, architectures and optimizers and cannot be explained using prior theory. Instead, we argue that the speedup comes from appropriate layer-wise norm growth, which can be achieved faster when the dataset size is smaller. We provide theoretical justification by analyzing the benefits of sampling biases induced by small datasets, and we present extensive empirical evidence supporting this hypothesis. Together, our results highlight the potential of unlocking more efficiency gain by jointly considering different scaling axes.</p>","absKo":"<p>데이터 스케일링이 자연적 한계에 가까워짐에 따라, 최근 연구들은 데이터 재사용의 잠재력을 탐구해 왔지만, 그것이 최적화에 미치는 영향은 여전히 충분히 이해되지 않고 있다. 본 연구는 데이터 반복이 compute 관점에서 학습 효율에 어떤 영향을 미치는지 살펴본다. 우리는 더 적은 데이터를 사용하면 더 빠른 수렴으로 이어질 수 있는 inverse-scaling effect를 조사하며, 이는 알고리즘적 task, architecture, optimizer 전반에서 관찰되고 기존 이론으로는 설명할 수 없다. 대신 우리는 이러한 속도 향상이 적절한 layer-wise norm growth에서 비롯된다고 주장하며, 이는 dataset size가 더 작을 때 더 빠르게 달성될 수 있다. 우리는 작은 dataset이 유도하는 sampling bias의 이점을 분석함으로써 이 주장에 대한 이론적 근거를 제시하고, 이를 뒷받침하는 광범위한 실험적 증거를 제시한다. 종합하면, 본 결과는 서로 다른 scaling 축을 함께 고려함으로써 더 큰 효율 향상을 끌어낼 잠재력이 있음을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"65378","en":"Spectral Reach: Understanding Neural Scaling through Kernel Alignment Dynamics","ko":"Spectral Reach: 커널 정합 동역학을 통한 신경 스케일링 이해","authors":"Konstantin Nikolaou, Jonas Scheunemann, Sven Krippendorf, Samuel Tovey, Christian Holm","pos":"#1302","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ECdZxuI9Hf","abs":"<p>Neural scaling laws describe predictable power-law relationships between model size, dataset size, compute cost, and performance. While these laws are applied to improve the performance of modern foundation models, the mechanisms underpinning them are less understood, in part due to the absence of scalable analysis tools. To this end, we introduce a framework for efficiently measuring the alignment between the empirical neural tangent kernel (eNTK) and loss residuals. Applying this framework to scaling experiments reveals a consistent pattern: larger and better-performing models exhibit <em>lower</em> kernel alignment throughout training. We interpret this <em>unalignment</em> through the lens of <em>spectral reach</em>: the capacity of a model to learn from progressively weaker spectral modes in its eNTK. This interpretation allows us to explain why larger models achieve lower losses: they sustain learning on weaker signals that smaller models cannot access. We further demonstrate that feature learning improves spectral reach and provide a mechanistic explanation of how this occurs, suggesting practical avenues for performance improvement.</p>"},{"id":"63645","en":"Size Transferability of Graph Convolutional Networks across Sparsity: A Generalized Graphon Perspective","ko":"희소성 전반의 graph convolutional network 크기 전이성: 일반화된 graphon 관점","authors":"Qinji Shu, Hang Sheng, Feng Ji, Hui Feng, Bo Hu","pos":"#1303","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=V3qt2V78ly","abs":"<p>Size transfer scales Graph Convolutional Networks (GCNs) by applying models trained on sampled subgraphs to larger target graphs. However, existing theoretical guarantees are typically confined to dense graphs or restricted sparsity regimes, failing to cover the arbitrary sparsity of real-world networks. To bridge this gap, we introduce the Generalized Graphon Convolutional Network (GWCN) based on the generalized graphon theory. Unlike the classical graphon limit which vanishes in sparse settings, GWCN employs stretching to construct a non-trivial limit that preserves topological structure. We derive an explicit transfer error bound that decomposes into size-dependent and density-dependent components, providing a unified guarantee across arbitrary sparsity levels. Empirical results on real-world networks corroborate our findings, demonstrating that transfer error vanishes as graph size increases and edge density decreases.</p>","absKo":"<p>Size transfer는 sampled subgraph에서 학습한 model을 더 큰 target graph에 적용하여 Graph Convolutional Networks(GCNs)를 확장한다. 그러나 기존 이론적 보장은 대체로 dense graph나 제한된 sparsity regime에 국한되어 있어, 실제 네트워크의 임의적 sparsity를 포괄하지 못한다. 이러한 간극을 메우기 위해 우리는 generalized graphon theory에 기반한 Generalized Graphon Convolutional Network(GWCN)을 도입한다. 희소한 설정에서 사라지는 classical graphon limit과 달리, GWCN은 stretching을 사용해 topological structure를 보존하는 non-trivial limit을 구성한다. 우리는 size-dependent component와 density-dependent component로 분해되는 명시적 transfer error bound를 유도하여, 임의의 sparsity 수준에 대해 통합된 보장을 제공한다. 실제 네트워크에서의 실험 결과는 우리의 발견을 뒷받침하며, graph size가 증가하고 edge density가 감소함에 따라 transfer error가 사라짐을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"62785","en":"Rethinking Convergence in MoE Training: The Role of Routing Sparsity","ko":"MoE Training에서 수렴 재고찰: Routing Sparsity의 역할","authors":"Weihao Zhu, Long Shi, Kang Wei, Zhe Wang, Yipeng Zhou, Haixia Zhang","pos":"#1304","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=dNLXIVeCqn","abs":"In Mixture-of-Experts (MoE) training, sparse routing, i.e., activating only the top-$K$ experts per token, is essential for balancing convergence speed and computational cost.  However, existing works typically choose $K$ empirically, without theoretical guidance. To address this gap, we characterize the convergence behavior of MoE training using stochastic optimization theory. Specifically, we derive a convergence upper bound of $\\mathcal{O}\\left(\\frac{1+M/K}{\\sqrt{T}}\\right)$, where $T$ is the number of training iterations and $M$ is the total number of experts per MoE layer. This result guarantees convergence and shows that increasing $K$ can accelerate training. By further fixing the total computational budget $R$ (in FLOPs), we obtain a refined bound of $\\mathcal{O}\\left(\\sqrt{\\frac{K}{R}} + \\frac{M}{\\sqrt{K R}}\\right)$, which is convex in $K$ and implies the existence of an optimal $K^{*}\\in[1,M]$ that achieves the best convergence performance. Extensive experiments validate our theoretical analysis under diverse settings.","absKo":"Mixture-of-Experts (MoE) training에서 sparse routing, 즉 token당 top-$K$ expert만 활성화하는 방식은 수렴 속도와 계산 비용의 균형을 맞추는 데 필수적이다. 그러나 기존 연구들은 일반적으로 $K$를 이론적 근거 없이 경험적으로 선택한다. 이 간극을 메우기 위해, 우리는 stochastic optimization theory를 사용하여 MoE training의 수렴 거동을 특성화한다. 구체적으로, 우리는 $\\mathcal{O}\\left(\\frac{1+M/K}{\\sqrt{T}}\\right)$의 수렴 상한을 유도하는데, 여기서 $T$는 training iteration 수이고 $M$은 각 MoE layer의 총 expert 수이다. 이 결과는 수렴을 보장하며 $K$를 증가시키면 학습이 더 빨라질 수 있음을 보여준다. 전체 계산 예산 $R$ (FLOPs)을 추가로 고정하면, 우리는 $\\mathcal{O}\\left(\\sqrt{\\frac{K}{R}} + \\frac{M}{\\sqrt{K R}}\\right)$의 refined bound를 얻는데, 이는 $K$에 대해 convex하며 최적의 수렴 성능을 달성하는 $K^{*}\\in[1,M]$의 존재를 시사한다. 광범위한 실험은 다양한 설정에서 우리의 이론 분석을 검증한다."},{"id":"66208","en":"Regularized Discriminative Alignment for Deep Representations under Label Shift","ko":"레이블 이동 하의 심층 표현을 위한 정규화 판별 정렬","authors":"Hengchao Shi, Boen Jiang, Guanhua Fang, Wen Yu, Ming Zheng","pos":"#1305","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=5m6GcVcqDO","abs":"<p>Label shift refers to the distribution shift scenario where the marginal label distribution changes while the class-conditional distribution remains invariant. To address this challenge in complex real-world settings, we propose <strong>Regularized Discriminative Alignment for Label Shift (RDALS)</strong>, a novel framework that adapts to target domains by aligning distributions within the deep latent space. By shifting the focus from raw inputs to learned representations, RDALS effectively operates under a weaker and more practical invariance assumption. Specifically, we construct a moment-matching linear system using Linear Discriminant Analysis (LDA) and show that this choice maximizes numerical stability. We further provide rigorous theoretical analysis, establishing finite-sample error bounds for the importance weight estimation and the generalization bounds for the adapted classifier. Extensive experiments on standard benchmarks demonstrate that RDALS significantly outperforms state-of-the-art baselines, achieving superior robustness and accuracy in both data-scarce and extreme-shift regimes.</p>"},{"id":"66255","en":"Partitioning for Intrinsic Model Inversion Resistance in Collaborative Inference","ko":"협업 추론에서 본질적 모델 역전 저항을 위한 분할","authors":"Rongke Liu, Youwen Zhu, Lei Zhou, Zhang Xianglong, Dong Wang","pos":"#1306","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=5NKJHteKPZ","abs":"In collaborative inference (CI), transmitting intermediate representations $Z$ from edge devices enables model inversion attacks (MIA) that reconstruct the original inputs $X$, while existing defenses mainly perturb shallow-layer $Z$ at the cost of utility. We instead ask: *where should an edge–cloud model be partitioned to obtain intrinsic resistance to MIA?* We challenge the intuition that depth is the driver of MIA resistance, and show that depth is sufficient only insofar as it enables a representational transition; this transition is necessary for *intrinsic* resistance and is marked by an abrupt rise in the lower bound of $H(X|Z)$. Correspondingly, the decisive variance term in the entropy bound shifts from a global variance to the intra-class mean-squared radius $R^2_c$ rather than dimensionality alone, yielding an $R^2_c$-based criterion to locate the transition zone, or identify it post hoc from MIA outcomes, which we term the *Golden Partition Zone* (GPZ). We further explain how $R^2_c$ evolves during training and show that it can be controlled through the label distribution; we refer to this controllable dynamics as the *Neural Vortex*. Across four representative deep vision models, partitioning at the GPZ yields over 4× higher reconstruction MSE compared to shallow splits; under entropy and inversion-model enhancements, decision-level representations provide 66\\% stronger resistance than feature-level ones, and we further observe that data type affects both the transition boundary and reconstruction."},{"id":"65728","en":"Over-Alignment vs Over-Fitting: The Role of Feature Learning Strength in Generalization","ko":"과잉 정렬 대 과적합: 일반화에서 특징 학습 강도의 역할","authors":"Taesun Yeom, Taehyeok Ha, Jaeho Lee","pos":"#1307","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Ak8sl1w550","abs":"<p>Feature learning strength (FLS), i.e., the inverse of the effective output scaling of a model, plays a critical role in shaping the optimization dynamics of neural nets. While its impact has been extensively studied under the asymptotic regimes---both in training time and FLS---existing theory offers limited insight into how FLS affects generalization in practical settings, such as when training is stopped upon reaching a target training risk. In this work, we investigate the impact of FLS on generalization in deep networks under such practical conditions. Through empirical studies, we first uncover the emergence of an <em>optimal FLS</em>---neither too small nor too large---that yields substantial generalization gains. This finding runs counter to the prevailing intuition that stronger feature learning universally improves generalization. To explain this phenomenon, we develop a theoretical analysis of gradient flow dynamics in two-layer ReLU nets trained with logistic loss, where FLS is controlled via initialization scale. Our main theoretical result establishes the existence of an optimal FLS arising from a trade-off between two competing effects: An excessively large FLS induces an <em>over-alignment</em> phenomenon that degrades generalization, while an overly small FLS leads to <em>over-fitting</em>.</p>"},{"id":"61225","en":"Optimal Self-Consistency for Efficient Reasoning with Large Language Models","ko":"Large Language Model의 효율적 추론을 위한 최적 Self-Consistency","authors":"Austin Feng, Marius Alonso, Ambroise Odonnat, Vasilii Feofanov, Ievgen Redko","pos":"#1308","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=sUTC7JE781","abs":"Self-consistency (SC) is a widely-used test-time inference technique for improving performance in chain-of-thought reasoning. It consists of generating multiple responses, or ``samples,\" from a large language model (LLM) and selecting the most frequent answer. This procedure can naturally be viewed as a majority vote or empirical mode estimation. Despite its effectiveness, self-consistency is prohibitively expensive at scale when naively applied to datasets, and it lacks a unified theoretical treatment of sample efficiency and scaling behavior.  In this paper, we provide the first comprehensive analysis of SC's scaling behavior and its variants, drawing on mode estimation and voting theory. We derive and empirically validate power law scaling for self-consistency across datasets, and analyze the sample efficiency for fixed-allocation and dynamic-allocation sampling schemes. From these insights, we introduce Blend-ASC, a novel variant of self-consistency that dynamically allocates samples to questions during inference, achieving state-of-the-art sample efficiency. Our approach uses $4.8\\times$ fewer samples than vanilla SC on average, outperforming both fixed- and dynamic-allocation SC baselines, thereby demonstrating the superiority of our approach in terms of efficiency. In contrast to existing variants, we note that Blend-ASC is hyperparameter-free and can fit any budget of samples, ensuring it can be easily applied to any self-consistency application.","absKo":"Self-consistency (SC)는 chain-of-thought reasoning의 성능을 향상시키기 위해 널리 쓰이는 test-time inference 기법이다. 이는 large language model (LLM)에서 여러 개의 응답, 즉 ``samples''를 생성한 뒤 가장 자주 나타나는 답을 선택하는 방식으로 구성된다. 이 절차는 자연스럽게 majority vote 또는 empirical mode estimation으로 볼 수 있다. 그 효과에도 불구하고, self-consistency는 dataset에 naïvely 적용할 경우 대규모에서 비용이 지나치게 크며, sample efficiency와 scaling behavior에 대한 통일된 이론적 설명도 부족하다. 본 논문에서는 mode estimation과 voting theory를 바탕으로 SC의 scaling behavior와 그 변형들에 대한 첫 포괄적 분석을 제공한다. 우리는 dataset 전반에서 self-consistency에 대해 power law scaling을 도출하고 실증적으로 검증하며, 고정 할당 및 동적 할당 sampling scheme의 sample efficiency를 분석한다. 이러한 통찰을 바탕으로, 우리는 inference 중 질문별로 sample을 동적으로 할당하는 새로운 self-consistency 변형인 Blend-ASC를 제안하며, 이를 통해 state-of-the-art sample efficiency를 달성한다. 우리의 접근은 vanilla SC보다 평균적으로 $4.8\\times$ 적은 sample을 사용하면서, 고정 및 동적 할당 SC baseline 모두를 능가하여 효율성 측면에서 우수함을 보여준다. 기존 변형들과 달리, Blend-ASC는 hyperparameter가 없고 어떤 sample budget에도 맞출 수 있어, 어떤 self-consistency application에도 쉽게 적용할 수 있다."},{"id":"62502","en":"Narrowing the ANN–SNN Gap for 1D Signal Classification with Multi-Scale Temporal Encoding and Sparsity-Regularized Transform Encoding","ko":"다중 스케일 시간 인코딩과 희소성 정규화 변환 인코딩으로 1D 신호 분류의 ANN–SNN 간극 축소","authors":"Qi Sun, Yulei Huang, Zhen Cao, Biao Hou","pos":"#1310","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=g0wATpD4Ic","abs":"Spiking neural networks (SNNs) promise energy-efficient inference, yet on static vision benchmarks they often trail matched ANNs under short simulation horizons. Under a matched-backbone and matched-budget protocol without extra tricks, we find that this ANN-SNN accuracy gap is consistently smaller on representative 1D signal classification benchmarks than on image benchmarks. We attribute this to a mechanism-level mismatch: leaky integration naturally implements causal evidence accumulation over time for native temporal signals, while static images typically require amplitude-to-spike encoding, whose finite-window estimation error becomes non-negligible at short horizons. Guided by this view, we propose a plug-and-play framework that combines Multi-Scale Temporal Encoding (MTE) and Sparsity-Regularized Transform Encoding (STE). MTE replaces naive repetition with multi-scale streams and allocates scale-aligned multi-bit integer spikes to increase per-step information density, and STE replaces a controllable fraction of LIF units with a transform-encoding neuron trained using auxiliary reconstruction and sparsity regularization, with a synthesis branch used only during training. Across diverse 1D datasets and backbone families, MTE$\\times$STE consistently improves the accuracy-efficiency trade-off over standard SNN baselines and matches or occasionally surpasses ANN counterparts.","absKo":"Spiking neural network (SNN)는 에너지 효율적인 inference를 약속하지만, static vision benchmark에서는 짧은 simulation horizon에서 matched ANN보다 성능이 뒤처지는 경우가 많다. extra trick이 없는 matched-backbone 및 matched-budget protocol에서, 우리는 대표적인 1D signal classification benchmark에서 이 ANN-SNN accuracy gap이 image benchmark보다 일관되게 작다는 점을 발견했다. 우리는 이를 mechanism-level mismatch로 설명한다. leaky integration은 native temporal signal에 대해 시간에 따른 causal evidence accumulation을 자연스럽게 구현하지만, static image는 일반적으로 amplitude-to-spike encoding이 필요하며, 이때 finite-window estimation error는 짧은 horizon에서 무시할 수 없게 된다. 이러한 관점에 따라 우리는 Multi-Scale Temporal Encoding (MTE)과 Sparsity-Regularized Transform Encoding (STE)를 결합한 plug-and-play framework를 제안한다. MTE는 단순 반복을 multi-scale stream으로 대체하고 scale-aligned multi-bit integer spike를 할당하여 step당 정보 밀도를 높이며, STE는 보조 reconstruction과 sparsity regularization으로 학습된 transform-encoding neuron을 사용하여 일부 LIF unit을 제어 가능하게 대체하고, synthesis branch는 학습 중에만 사용한다. 다양한 1D dataset과 backbone family 전반에서 MTE$\\times$STE는 표준 SNN baseline보다 accuracy-efficiency trade-off를 일관되게 개선하며, ANN 대응 모델과 같거나 때로는 이를 능가한다."},{"id":"64965","en":"Gradient Flow Dynamics and Implicit Bias of Diagonal Linear Networks under Infinitesimal Initialization","ko":"무한소 초기화 하의 Diagonal Linear Network의 Gradient Flow 동역학과 Implicit Bias","authors":"Jiajie Zhao, Jianxing Wang, Junjie Yang, Zhiwei Bai, Yaoyu Zhang","pos":"#1311","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=IJph1t3Egr","abs":"<p>We study the gradient flow dynamics of diagonal linear networks for regression tasks under infinitesimal initialization. Extending the saddle-to-saddle dynamics described in Theorem 1 from Pesme &amp; Flammarion (2023), we generalize the analysis to both deep diagonal linear networks and a broader class of two-layer diagonal linear networks (as defined in Definition 4.1). Specifically, we demonstrate that the training trajectories of these models can be equivalently characterized by the proposed Algorithm 1. We further prove that this algorithm converges to the solution of a modified ℓ1 norm minimization problem. As a result, we establish that the implicit bias of both network architectures corresponds to a modified ℓ1 norm in the regime of infinitesimal initialization. Additionally, we provide insights into the underlying mechanisms governing these dynamics by identifying the Structural Invariant Manifold (SIM) (Zhao et al., 2025) as the key geometric structure that shapes the learning process</p>"},{"id":"62102","en":"Explaining Data Mixing Scaling Laws","ko":"데이터 믹싱 Scaling Law 설명하기","authors":"Rui Dai, SHURAN ZHENG","pos":"#1312","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=joReaAnwnH","abs":"<p>Recent research has established empirical scaling laws to predict model performance on multi-domain data mixtures. However, a theoretical understanding of these model loss behaviors remains limited. In this work, we propose a unified framework to explain the underlying mechanics of data mixing. Our approach extends theoretical perspectives originally developed for standard neural scaling laws (e.g., Kaplan and Chinchilla) to the multi-domain setting. Based on the distributional assumption that domains overlap on fundamental skills while diverging on specialized skills, we identify two key factors that decide the domain loss of models trained on different data mixtures: Capacity Competition, where the allocation of finite model capacity couples domain losses globally, and Noise Reduction, where optimal weights shift toward harder-to-learn domains to minimize variance. Experiments demonstrate that our framework fits the loss landscape with lower Mean Relative Error than existing empirical baselines and accurately predicts optimal training mixtures. Crucially, our model achieves these results using significantly fewer  parameters.</p>","absKo":"<p>최근 연구들은 다중 도메인 데이터 혼합에서 모델 성능을 예측하기 위한 경험적 scaling law를 확립했다. 그러나 이러한 모델 loss 거동에 대한 이론적 이해는 여전히 제한적이다. 본 연구에서는 데이터 혼합의 근본 메커니즘을 설명하기 위한 통합 프레임워크를 제안한다. 우리의 접근은 표준 neural scaling law(예: Kaplan 및 Chinchilla)를 위해 원래 개발된 이론적 관점을 다중 도메인 설정으로 확장한다. 도메인들이 기초적 기술에서는 겹치지만 전문화된 기술에서는 분기된다는 분포 가정에 기반하여, 서로 다른 데이터 혼합으로 학습된 모델의 domain loss를 결정하는 두 가지 핵심 요인을 식별한다. 첫째, Capacity Competition은 유한한 모델 용량의 배분이 domain loss를 전역적으로 결합하는 현상이고, 둘째, Noise Reduction은 분산을 최소화하기 위해 최적 가중치가 더 학습하기 어려운 도메인 쪽으로 이동하는 현상이다. 실험은 우리의 프레임워크가 기존 경험적 baseline보다 더 낮은 Mean Relative Error로 loss landscape에 적합하며, 최적 학습 혼합을 정확하게 예측함을 보여준다. 특히, 우리의 모델은 훨씬 더 적은 파라미터를 사용하여 이러한 결과를 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"64453","en":"Dynamics Reveals Structure: Challenging the Linear Propagation Assumption","ko":"동역학이 구조를 드러낸다: 선형 전파 가정에 대한 도전","authors":"Hoyeon Chang, Bálint Mucsányi, Seong Joon Oh","pos":"#1313","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=NTd7TQYQkX","abs":"<p>Neural networks adapt through first-order parameter updates, yet it remains unclear whether such updates preserve logical coherence. We investigate the geometric limits of the Linear Propagation Assumption (LPA), the premise that local updates coherently propagate to logical consequences. To formalize this, we adopt relation algebra and study three core operations on relations: negation flips truth values, converse swaps argument order, and composition chains relations. For negation and converse, we prove that guaranteeing direction-agnostic first-order propagation necessitates a tensor factorization separating entity-pair context from relation content. However, for composition, we identify a fundamental obstruction. We show that composition reduces to conjunction, and prove that any conjunction well-defined on linear features must be bilinear. Since bilinearity is incompatible with negation, this forces the feature map to collapse. These results suggest that failures in knowledge editing, the reversal curse, and multi-hop reasoning may stem from common structural limitations inherent to the LPA.</p>","absKo":"<p>Neural network는 first-order parameter update를 통해 적응하지만, 그러한 update가 logical coherence를 보존하는지는 여전히 불분명하다. 우리는 local update가 logical consequence로 일관되게 전파된다는 전제인 Linear Propagation Assumption (LPA)의 기하학적 한계를 조사한다. 이를 정식화하기 위해 relation algebra를 채택하고, 관계에 대한 세 가지 핵심 연산을 연구한다: negation은 truth value를 뒤집고, converse는 argument order를 바꾸며, composition은 relation을 연결한다. negation과 converse에 대해서는, direction-agnostic first-order propagation을 보장하려면 entity-pair context와 relation content를 분리하는 tensor factorization이 필요함을 증명한다. 그러나 composition에 대해서는 근본적인 장애물을 확인한다. 우리는 composition이 conjunction으로 환원됨을 보이고, linear feature 위에서 잘 정의되는 모든 conjunction은 bilinear여야 함을 증명한다. bilinearity는 negation과 양립할 수 없으므로, 이는 feature map이 붕괴하도록 강제한다. 이러한 결과는 knowledge editing의 실패, reversal curse, 그리고 multi-hop reasoning이 LPA에 내재된 공통의 구조적 한계에서 비롯될 수 있음을 시사한다.</p>"},{"id":"61565","en":"Decomposing Out-of-Distribution Error in Conditional Flow Matching via Wasserstein Geometry","ko":"Wasserstein Geometry를 통한 Conditional Flow Matching의 Out-of-Distribution Error 분해","authors":"Long HC Pham","pos":"#1315","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=orzcDIBxa0","abs":"<p>Conditional flow matching has emerged as a powerful generative modeling framework that learns a vector field to transport an initial distribution toward a target data distribution. However, theoretical understanding of its out-of-distribution (OOD) performance under unseen conditions remains limited. In this work, we establish a rigorous geometric formulation to decompose the source of generalization error. We treat the conditional task as a map from the condition space to the Wasserstein space and derive a generalization bound under a coarse embedding assumption. The resulting decomposition separates OOD error into three tractable components: <em>Interpolation Sparsity</em>, <em>Geometric Distortion</em>, and <em>In-Distribution Fit</em>. Our empirical evaluation confirms that this framework demonstrates three key functions: (1) it acts as a diagnostic tool that tracks the dynamics of generalization during training; (2) it identifies dataset-specific failure modes (e.g., topological gaps, geometric instability); and (3) it enables mathematically motivated interventions that yield predictable gains by minimizing specific terms.</p>","absKo":"<p>Conditional flow matching은 초기 분포를 목표 데이터 분포로 이동시키는 vector field를 학습하는 강력한 generative modeling framework로 부상했다. 그러나 보지 못한 조건에서의 out-of-distribution (OOD) 성능에 대한 이론적 이해는 여전히 제한적이다. 본 연구에서는 generalization error의 근원을 분해하기 위한 엄밀한 기하학적 formulation을 정립한다. 우리는 conditional task를 condition space에서 Wasserstein space로의 map으로 다루고, coarse embedding assumption 하에서 generalization bound를 유도한다. 그 결과 얻어진 분해는 OOD error를 세 가지 다루기 가능한 구성요소로 분리한다: <em>Interpolation Sparsity</em>, <em>Geometric Distortion</em>, 그리고 <em>In-Distribution Fit</em>. 우리의 실험적 평가는 이 framework가 세 가지 핵심 기능을 수행함을 확인한다: (1) 학습 중 generalization의 동역학을 추적하는 진단 도구로 작동한다; (2) dataset-specific failure mode(예: topological gap, geometric instability)를 식별한다; (3) 특정 항을 최소화함으로써 예측 가능한 성능 향상을 이끄는 수학적으로 동기 부여된 개입을 가능하게 한다.</p>"},{"id":"61585","en":"$\\mathcal{O}(\\log N)$ Latent Dimension Suffices for Universal Approximation of Permutation-invariant Function","ko":"Permutation-Invariant Function의 Universal Approximation에는 $\\mathcal{O}(\\log N)$ Latent Dimension이면 충분하다","authors":"Min ZHOU, Enming Liang, Minghua Chen","pos":"#1412","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ojghzKHmLw","abs":"Learning permutation-invariant functions over sets of $N$ elements is fundamental to many deep learning applications. While sum-decomposable architectures like DeepSets theoretically offer universal approximation capabilities for such functions, existing constructive bounds suggest that the latent dimension must grow linearly with the set size, i.e., $\\mathcal{O}(N)$. This linear scaling poses a significant bottleneck for scalability. In this paper, we break this theoretical barrier by proving that a latent dimension of $\\mathcal{O}(\\log N)$ suffices for the universal approximation of Wasserstein-stable permutation-invariant functions. We establish this by first showing that the covering number of the Wasserstein space scales linearly with $N$. Then,  we show that random embeddings, specifically Random Fourier Features, with a logarithmic latent dimension to the covering number can preserve the geometry with high probability, thereby guaranteeing the existence of deterministic embeddings of the same width. This result advances the understanding of the expressivity of set-based neural network architectures.","absKo":"집합에 속한 $N$개의 원소에 대해 permutation-invariant function을 학습하는 것은 많은 deep learning application에서 핵심적이다. DeepSets와 같은 sum-decomposable architecture는 이론적으로 이러한 function에 대한 universal approximation capability를 제공하지만, 기존의 구성적 bound는 latent dimension이 집합 크기에 비례하여, 즉 $\\mathcal{O}(N)$으로 커져야 함을 시사한다. 이러한 선형 스케일링은 scalability에 큰 병목을 만든다. 본 논문에서는 Wasserstein-stable permutation-invariant function의 universal approximation에 latent dimension $\\mathcal{O}(\\log N)$이면 충분하다는 것을 증명함으로써 이 이론적 장벽을 허문다. 이를 위해 먼저 Wasserstein space의 covering number가 $N$에 선형적으로 스케일함을 보인다. سپس, random embedding, 특히 Random Fourier Features가 covering number에 대해 로그 크기의 latent dimension을 가지면서 높은 확률로 geometry를 보존할 수 있음을 보이고, 이를 통해 동일한 width를 갖는 deterministic embedding의 존재를 보장한다. 이 결과는 set-based neural network architecture의 expressivity에 대한 이해를 진전시킨다."},{"id":"65424","en":"Approximate Equivariance via Projection-Based Regularisation","ko":"Projection 기반 정규화를 통한 근사 Equivariance","authors":"Torben Berndt, Jan Stuehmer","pos":"#1414","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Dly6gCtE4V","abs":"<p>Equivariance is a powerful inductive bias in neural networks, improving generalisation and physical consistency. Recently, however, non-equivariant models have regained attention, due to their better runtime performance and imperfect symmetries that might arise in real-world applications. This has motivated the development of approximately equivariant models that strike a middle ground between respecting symmetries and fitting the data distribution. Existing approaches in this field either rely on sampling from a group, incurring a high sample complexity, or explicitly parameterise a model as a sum of an equivariant and non-equivariant network.    This work instead approaches approximate equivariance via a projection-based regulariser which leverages a layer-wise orthogonal decomposition of a network's layers into equivariant and non-equivariant components. In contrast to existing methods, this penalises non-equivariance at an operator level across the full group orbit, rather than point-wise as in sample-based approaches. We present a mathematical framework for computing the non-equivariance penalty exactly and efficiently in both the spatial and spectral domains. In our experiments, our method consistently outperforms prior approximate equivariance approaches in both model performance and efficiency, achieving substantial runtime gains over sample-based regularisers.</p>"},{"id":"62225","en":"Branch Scaling Manifests as Implicit Architectural Regularization for Improving Generalization in Overparameterized ResNets","ko":"Branch Scaling은 과파라미터화 ResNet에서 일반화 향상을 위한 암묵적 아키텍처 정규화로 나타남","authors":"Zixiong Yu, Guhan Chen, Jianfa Lai, Bohan Li, Songtao Tian","pos":"#1416","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=iWV5o07Bxv","abs":"<p>Scaling factors in residual branches have emerged as a prevalent method for boosting neural network performance, especially in normalization-free architectures. While prior work has primarily examined scaling effects from an optimization perspective, this paper investigates their role in residual architectures through the lens of generalization theory. Specifically, we establish that wide residual networks (ResNets) with constant scaling factors become asymptotically unlearnable as depth increases. In contrast, when the scaling factor exhibits rapid depth-wise decay combined with early stopping, over-parameterized ResNets achieve minimax-optimal generalization rates. To establish this, we demonstrate that the generalization capability of wide ResNets can be approximated by the kernel regression associated with a specific kernel. Our theoretical findings are validated through experiments on synthetic data and real-world classification tasks, including MNIST and CIFAR-100.</p>","absKo":"<p>residual branch의 scaling factor는 특히 normalization-free architecture에서 neural network 성능을 향상시키는 널리 쓰이는 방법으로 부상했다. 기존 연구가 주로 optimization 관점에서 scaling 효과를 살펴본 반면, 본 논문은 generalization theory의 관점에서 residual architecture에서의 역할을 조사한다. 구체적으로, constant scaling factor를 갖는 wide residual network(ResNet)는 depth가 증가할수록 점근적으로 학습 불가능해짐을 보인다. 반대로, scaling factor가 빠르게 depth-wise decay하고 early stopping과 결합될 때, over-parameterized ResNet은 minimax-optimal generalization rate를 달성한다. 이를 보이기 위해, wide ResNet의 generalization 능력은 특정 kernel과 연관된 kernel regression으로 근사될 수 있음을 입증한다. 우리의 이론적 결과는 synthetic data와 MNIST 및 CIFAR-100을 포함한 실제 분류 task에 대한 실험을 통해 검증된다.</p>"},{"id":"64436","en":"Possibilistic Predictive Uncertainty for Deep Learning","ko":"딥러닝을 위한 가능성론적 예측 불확실성","authors":"Yao Ni, Jeremie Houssineau, Yew Soon ONG, Piotr Koniusz","pos":"#1504","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=NhL0mBNFk4","abs":"<p>Deep neural networks achieve impressive results across diverse applications, yet their overconfidence on unseen inputs necessitates reliable epistemic uncertainty modelling. Existing methods for uncertainty modelling face a fundamental dilemma: Bayesian approaches provide principled estimates but remain computationally prohibitive, while efficient second-order predictors lack rigorous derivations connecting their specific objectives to epistemic uncertainty quantification. To resolve this dilemma, we introduce <strong>D</strong>irichlet-<strong>a</strong>pproximated <strong>p</strong>ossibilistic <strong>p</strong>osterior p<strong>r</strong>edictions (DAPPr), a principled framework leveraging possibility theory. We define a possibilistic posterior over parameters, projects this posterior to the prediction space via supremum operators, and approximates the projected posterior using learnable Dirichlet possibility functions. This projection-and-approximation strategy yields a simple training objective with closed-form solutions. Extensive experiments across diverse benchmarks demonstrate that our approach achieves competitive or superior uncertainty quantification performance compared to state-of-the-art evidential deep learning methods while maintaining both principled derivation and computational efficiency. Code will be available upon acceptance.</p>","absKo":"<p>Deep neural network는 다양한 응용에서 인상적인 결과를 달성하지만, 보지 못한 입력에 대한 과도한 자신감은 신뢰할 수 있는 epistemic uncertainty modelling을 필요로 한다. uncertainty modelling을 위한 기존 방법들은 근본적인 딜레마에 직면한다. Bayesian 접근법은 원칙적인 추정을 제공하지만 계산 비용이 너무 크고, 효율적인 second-order predictor는 특정 objective가 epistemic uncertainty quantification과 어떻게 연결되는지에 대한 엄밀한 유도 과정을 결여한다. 이 딜레마를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 possibility theory를 활용하는 원칙적인 프레임워크인 <strong>D</strong>irichlet-<strong>a</strong>pproximated <strong>p</strong>ossibilistic <strong>p</strong>osterior p<strong>r</strong>edictions (DAPPr)를 제안한다. 우리는 parameter에 대한 possibilistic posterior를 정의하고, supremum operator를 통해 이 posterior를 prediction space로 사상한 뒤, learnable Dirichlet possibility function을 사용해 사상된 posterior를 근사한다. 이러한 projection-and-approximation 전략은 closed-form solution을 갖는 단순한 training objective를 제공한다. 다양한 benchmark에 걸친 광범위한 실험은 우리의 접근법이 원칙적인 유도와 계산 효율성을 유지하면서, state-of-the-art evidential deep learning 방법과 비교해 경쟁력 있거나 더 우수한 uncertainty quantification 성능을 달성함을 보여준다. 코드는 승인 시 공개될 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"63559","en":"Operationalizing the Superficial Alignment Hypothesis via Task Complexity","ko":"과제 복잡성을 통한 표면적 정렬 가설의 실천적 해석","authors":"Tomás Vergara Browne, Darshan Patil, Ivan Titov, Siva Reddy, Tiago Pimentel, Marius Mosbach","pos":"#1904","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=W1P3l4rI60","abs":"<p>The superficial alignment hypothesis (SAH) posits that large language models learn most of their knowledge during pre-training, and that post-training merely surfaces this knowledge. The SAH, however, lacks a precise definition, which has led to (i) different and seemingly orthogonal arguments supporting it, and (ii) important critiques to it. We propose a new metric called <strong>Task Complexity</strong>: the length of the shortest program that achieves a target performance on a task. In this framework, the SAH claims that pre-trained models drastically reduce the task complexity of achieving high performance on many tasks. Our definition unifies prior arguments supporting the SAH, interpreting them as different strategies to find such short programs. Experimentally, we estimate task complexities of mathematical reasoning, machine translation, and instruction following tasks and show that their respective task complexities can be remarkably low when conditioned on a pre-trained model. Further, we find that pre-training enables access to strong performances on our tasks, but it can require programs of gigabytes of length to access them. Post-training, on the other hand, collapses the complexity of reaching this same performance by several orders of magnitude. Overall, our results highlight that task adaptation can require remarkably little information—often just a few kilobytes.</p>","absKo":"superficial alignment hypothesis (SAH)는 대규모 언어 모델이 대부분의 지식을 pre-training 동안 학습하며, post-training은 단지 이 지식을 표면화할 뿐이라고 주장한다. 그러나 SAH는 정밀한 정의가 부족하여, (i) 이를 지지하는 서로 다르고 겉보기에는 직교하는 논의들이 존재하고, (ii) 이에 대한 중요한 비판들도 제기되어 왔다. 우리는 <strong>Task Complexity</strong>라는 새로운 지표를 제안한다. 이는 어떤 task에서 목표 성능을 달성하는 가장 짧은 program의 길이다. 이 틀에서 SAH는 pre-trained model이 많은 task에서 높은 성능을 달성하는 데 필요한 task complexity를 크게 줄인다고 주장한다. 우리의 정의는 SAH를 지지하는 기존 논의를 통합하며, 이를 그러한 짧은 program을 찾기 위한 서로 다른 전략으로 해석한다. 실험적으로 우리는 수학적 추론, machine translation, instruction following task의 task complexity를 추정하고, pre-trained model에 조건부로 주어졌을 때 이들의 task complexity가 놀라울 정도로 낮아질 수 있음을 보인다. 또한 pre-training은 우리의 task에서 강력한 성능에 접근할 수 있게 하지만, 그 성능에 도달하기 위해 gigabyte 길이의 program이 필요할 수 있음을 발견했다. 반면 post-training은 같은 성능에 도달하는 complexity를 여러 자릿수만큼 붕괴시킨다. 전반적으로, 우리의 결과는 task adaptation에 놀라울 정도로 적은 정보, 종종 몇 kilobyte만으로도 충분할 수 있음을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"66751","en":"Learning to Approximate Uniform Facility Location via Graph Neural Networks","ko":"Graph Neural Network를 통한 Uniform Facility Location 근사 학습","authors":"Chendi Qian, Christopher Morris, Stefanie Jegelka, Christian Sohler","pos":"#2415","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=0dmd06JuBr","abs":"<p>There has been a growing interest in using neural networks, especially message-passing neural networks (MPNNs), to solve hard combinatorial optimization problems heuristically. However, existing learning-based approaches for hard combinatorial optimization tasks often rely on supervised training data, reinforcement learning, or gradient estimators, leading to significant computational overhead, unstable training, or a lack of provable performance guarantees. In contrast, classical approximation algorithms offer such performance guarantees under worst-case inputs but are non-differentiable and unable to adaptively exploit structural regularities in natural input distributions. We address this dichotomy with the fundamental example of Uniform Facility Location (UniFL), a variant of the combinatorial facility location problem with applications in clustering, data summarization, logistics and supply chain design. We develop a fully differentiable MPNN model that embeds approximation-algorithmic principles while avoiding the need for solver supervision or discrete relaxations. Our approach admits provable approximation and size generalization guarantees to much larger instances than seen during training. Empirically, we show that our approach outperforms standard non-learned approximation algorithms in terms of solution quality, closing the gap with computationally intensive integer linear programming approaches. Overall, this work provides a step toward bridging learning-based methods and approximation algorithms for discrete optimization.</p>"},{"id":"61716","en":"Weak-to-Strong Generalization via Bregman Bias–Variance Decomposition","ko":"Bregman Bias-Variance 분해를 통한 Weak-to-Strong 일반화","authors":"Gengze Xu, Wei Yao, Ziqiao Wang, Yong Liu","pos":"#3411","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=nWxUhxv4d8","abs":"<p>Weak-to-strong generalization (W2SG) is the phenomenon in which a powerful student model, trained on labels produced by a weaker teacher, ultimately outperforms the teacher on the target task. In this work, we theoretically investigate how W2SG can arise via a generalized bias–variance decomposition under Bregman divergence. We show that the expected population risk gap between the student and the teacher is characterized by the expected misfit between the two models. Unlike earlier misfit-based analyses, our theory removes several restrictive assumptions, e.g., it does not require the student hypothesis class to be convex. Our results indicate that W2SG is more likely when the student effectively approximates the teacher's posterior mean. Specializing to squared loss, we provide a sufficient condition  (illustrated through a concrete example) under which the student converges to its posterior mean teacher; in particular, increasing the student model size can ensure this convergence. For cross-entropy loss, our analysis further suggests that lowering the entropy of the student's predictive distribution can promote W2SG. We also find that the reverse cross-entropy, unlike the standard forward cross-entropy, is less sensitive to the teacher's predictive uncertainty. Finally, we verify these theoretical insights empirically and demonstrate that incorporating reverse cross-entropy consistently improves student performance.</p>","absKo":"<p>Weak-to-strong generalization (W2SG)은 약한 teacher가 생성한 label로 학습된 강력한 student model이 결국 target task에서 teacher를 능가하는 현상을 말한다. 본 연구에서는 Bregman divergence 하에서 일반화된 bias–variance decomposition을 통해 W2SG가 어떻게 나타날 수 있는지를 이론적으로 살펴본다. 우리는 student와 teacher 사이의 기대 population risk gap이 두 모델 간의 기대 misfit에 의해 특징지어진다는 것을 보인다. 이전의 misfit 기반 분석과 달리, 우리의 이론은 몇 가지 제한적인 가정을 제거하며, 예를 들어 student hypothesis class가 convex일 필요가 없다. 우리의 결과는 student가 teacher의 posterior mean을 효과적으로 근사할 때 W2SG가 더 일어나기 쉽다는 점을 시사한다. squared loss에 특화하여, 우리는 student가 posterior mean teacher로 수렴하는 충분조건을 구체적인 예시와 함께 제시한다. 특히 student model size를 늘리면 이러한 수렴을 보장할 수 있다. cross-entropy loss의 경우, 우리의 분석은 student의 predictive distribution entropy를 낮추는 것이 W2SG를 촉진할 수 있음을 추가로 시사한다. 또한 standard forward cross-entropy와 달리 reverse cross-entropy는 teacher의 predictive uncertainty에 덜 민감함을 확인한다. 마지막으로, 이러한 이론적 통찰을 실험적으로 검증하고 reverse cross-entropy를 포함하면 student 성능이 일관되게 향상됨을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"61650","en":"Efficient Learning of Compositional Targets with Hierarchical Spectral Methods","ko":"계층적 스펙트럴 방법을 통한 조합적 타깃의 효율적 학습","authors":"Hugo Tabanelli, Yatin Dandi, Luca Pesce, FLORENT KRZAKALA","pos":"#3413","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=o4w4LRrIMT","abs":"<p>Why depth yields a genuine computational advantage over shallow methods remains a central open question in learning theory. We study this question in a controlled high-dimensional Gaussian setting, focusing on compositional target functions. We analyze their learnability using an explicit three-layer fitting model trained via layer-wise spectral estimators. Although the target is globally a high-degree polynomial, its compositional structure allows learning to proceed in stages: an intermediate representation reveals structure that is inaccessible at the input level. This reduces learning to simpler spectral estimation problems, well studied in the context of multi-index models, whereas any shallow estimator must resolve all components simultaneously. Our analysis relies on Gaussian universality, leading to sharp separations in sample complexity between two and three-layer learning strategies.</p>","absKo":"<p>depth가 shallow method에 비해 진정한 computational advantage를 제공하는 이유는 학습 이론의 중심적인 열린 질문으로 남아 있다. 우리는 compositional target function에 초점을 맞춘 통제된 고차원 Gaussian setting에서 이 질문을 연구한다. 우리는 layer-wise spectral estimator로 학습되는 명시적 three-layer fitting model을 사용해 그 learnability를 분석한다. target은 전역적으로는 고차 다항식이지만, compositional structure 덕분에 학습은 단계적으로 진행될 수 있다. 즉, 중간 표현이 input level에서는 접근할 수 없는 구조를 드러낸다. 이로 인해 학습 문제는 multi-index model 맥락에서 잘 연구된 더 단순한 spectral estimation problem으로 축소되는 반면, shallow estimator는 모든 구성 요소를 동시에 해결해야 한다. 우리의 분석은 Gaussian universality에 의존하며, 두 layer와 세 layer 학습 전략 사이에 샘플 복잡도에서 날카로운 분리를 이끈다.</p>"},{"id":"62983","en":"Functional Equivalence in Attention: A Comprehensive Study with Applications to Linear Mode Connectivity","ko":"Attention의 기능적 동치성: Linear Mode Connectivity 응용을 포함한 종합 연구","authors":"Viet Hoang Tran, VINH KHANH BUI, Van-Hoan Trinh, Ngoc Tan Lai, Tan Nguyen","pos":"#3607","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=bG4ZzflPCt","abs":"<p>Neural network parameter spaces are inherently non-injective, as distinct parameter configurations can realize identical functions through functional equivalence. While this symmetry is well understood in classical fully connected and convolutional models, it becomes substantially more intricate in modern attention-based architectures. Existing analyses of multihead attention have largely focused on the vanilla formulation, overlooking positional encodings that fundamentally reshape architectural symmetries. In this work, we provide a formal study of functional equivalence in Transformers with positional encodings. Focusing on the two most widely used variants--sinusoidal and rotary positional encodings (RoPE)--we show that sinusoidal encodings preserve the equivalence structure of vanilla attention, whereas rotary encodings significantly reduce the symmetry group, thereby enhancing expressivity. This offers a principled explanation for the growing prominence of RoPE in practice. We further examine how positional encodings affect linear mode connectivity, and through an alignment algorithm, empirically demonstrate that the presence and variability of connectivity across Transformer settings crucially depend on the positional encoding.</p>","absKo":"<p>신경망 파라미터 공간은 본질적으로 non-injective하다. 서로 다른 parameter configuration이 functional equivalence를 통해 동일한 함수를 실현할 수 있기 때문이다. 이러한 대칭성은 고전적인 fully connected 모델과 convolutional 모델에서는 잘 이해되어 있지만, 현대의 attention-based architecture에서는 훨씬 더 복잡해진다. 기존의 multihead attention 분석은 주로 vanilla formulation에 초점을 맞추어 왔으며, architectural symmetry를 근본적으로 재구성하는 positional encoding은 간과해 왔다. 본 연구에서는 positional encoding이 있는 Transformer에서의 functional equivalence를 형식적으로 연구한다. 가장 널리 사용되는 두 가지 변형인 sinusoidal positional encoding과 rotary positional encoding(RoPE)에 초점을 맞추어, sinusoidal encoding은 vanilla attention의 equivalence structure를 보존하는 반면 rotary encoding은 symmetry group을 크게 축소하여 expressivity를 향상시킨다는 것을 보인다. 이는 실제로 RoPE의 중요성이 커지고 있는 현상을 원리적으로 설명해 준다. 또한 positional encoding이 linear mode connectivity에 어떤 영향을 미치는지도 살펴보고, alignment algorithm을 통해 Transformer setting 전반에서 connectivity의 존재와 변동성이 positional encoding에 결정적으로 의존함을 실증적으로 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"63711","en":"Pruning at Initialisation through the lens of Graphon Limit: Convergence, Expressivity, and Generalisation","ko":"Graphon Limit 관점의 초기화 시 Pruning: 수렴성, 표현력, 일반화","authors":"Hoang Pham, The-Anh Ta, Long Tran-Thanh","pos":"#3912","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=UOpsG95XqH","abs":"<p>Pruning at Initialisation methods discover sparse, trainable subnetworks before training, but their theoretical mechanisms remain elusive. Existing analyses are often limited to finite-width statistics, lacking a rigorous characterisation of the global sparsity patterns that emerge as networks grow large. In this work, we connect discrete pruning heuristics to graph limit theory via graphons, establishing the <em>graphon limit of PaI masks</em>. We introduce a <em>Factorised Saliency Model</em> that encompasses popular pruning criteria and prove that, under regularity conditions, the discrete masks generated by these algorithms converge to deterministic bipartite graphons. This limit framework establishes a novel topological taxonomy for sparse networks: while unstructured methods (e.g., Random, Magnitude) converge to homogeneous graphons representing uniform connectivity, data-driven methods (e.g., SNIP, GraSP) converge to heterogeneous graphons that encode implicit feature selection. Leveraging this continuous characterisation, we derive two fundamental theoretical results: (i) a Universal Approximation Theorem for sparse networks that depends only on the intrinsic dimension of active coordinate subspaces; and (ii) a Graphon-NTK generalisation bound demonstrating how the limit graphon modulates the kernel geometry to align with informative features. Our results transform the study of sparse neural networks from combinatorial graph problems into a rigorous framework of continuous operators, offering a new mechanism for analysing expressivity and generalisation in sparse neural networks.</p>","absKo":"초기화 시 Pruning (Pruning at Initialisation, PaI) 방법은 훈련 전에 sparse하고 학습 가능한 subnetwork를 발견하지만, 그 이론적 메커니즘은 여전히 불분명하다. 기존 분석은 유한 폭 통계에 제한되는 경우가 많아, 네트워크가 커질 때 나타나는 전역 sparsity pattern을 엄밀하게 특성화하지 못한다. 본 연구에서는 graphon을 통해 discrete pruning heuristic을 graph limit theory와 연결하여, <em>PaI mask의 graphon limit</em>을 확립한다. 우리는 널리 쓰이는 pruning criterion을 포괄하는 <em>Factorised Saliency Model</em>을 도입하고, regularity condition 하에서 이 알고리즘들이 생성하는 discrete mask가 결정론적 bipartite graphon으로 수렴함을 증명한다. 이 극한 프레임워크는 sparse network에 대한 새로운 위상학적 분류를 확립한다: Random, Magnitude와 같은 unstructured method는 균일한 연결을 나타내는 homogeneous graphon으로 수렴하는 반면, SNIP, GraSP와 같은 data-driven method는 암묵적 feature selection을 인코딩하는 heterogeneous graphon으로 수렴한다. 이러한 연속적 특성화를 활용하여, 우리는 두 가지 근본적인 이론적 결과를 도출한다: (i) 활성 coordinate subspace의 내재 차원에만 의존하는 sparse network에 대한 Universal Approximation Theorem; (ii) limit graphon이 kernel geometry를 유익한 feature와 정렬되도록 어떻게 조절하는지를 보여주는 Graphon-NTK generalisation bound. 우리의 결과는 sparse neural network 연구를 조합론적 graph 문제에서 연속 연산자의 엄밀한 프레임워크로 전환하며, sparse neural network의 표현력과 일반화를 분석하는 새로운 메커니즘을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"63845","en":"The Implicit Bias of Depth: From Neural Collapse to Softmax Codes","ko":"깊이의 암묵적 편향: neural collapse에서 softmax code까지","authors":"Connall Garrod, Jonathan Keating, Christos Thrampoulidis","pos":"#4508","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=TDaVoBfTjY","abs":"<p>Neural collapse (NC) describes the structured geometry that emerges in the features and weights of trained classifiers. Recent theory suggests NC can be suboptimal in deep architectures, attributing this to an explicit low-rank bias from L2 regularization. We study the deep unconstrained feature model (UFM)—equivalent to a deep linear network with orthogonal inputs—trained without regularization, to isolate how gradient descent and depth alone shape NC. We show that depth induces an implicit low-rank bias: low-rank matrices propagate norm more efficiently through successive multiplications, promoting low-rank alternatives to NC. These alternatives, we argue, correspond to softmax codes: max-margin solutions previously found in width-bottlenecked networks. Analyzing training dynamics under spectral initialization, we identify an early-time repulsion among singular values that drives low-rank emergence, and characterize how depth shrinks NC's basin of attraction. Finally, we show that some effects act in the opposite direction: for randomly initialized networks, increasing width biases training toward higher-rank solutions. Our results provide the first asymptotic and dynamic characterization of implicit bias in deep UFMs trained with unregularized multiclass cross-entropy.</p>","absKo":"<p>Neural collapse (NC)는 학습된 classifier의 feature와 weight에서 나타나는 구조화된 기하를 설명한다. 최근 이론은 deep architecture에서 NC가 suboptimal일 수 있으며, 그 원인을 L2 regularization에 의한 명시적 low-rank bias로 돌린다. 우리는 정규화 없이 학습된 deep unconstrained feature model (UFM)을, orthogonal input을 갖는 deep linear network와 동등한 모델로 두고, gradient descent와 depth만이 NC를 어떻게 형성하는지 분리하여 연구한다. 우리는 depth가 implicit low-rank bias를 유도함을 보인다. 즉, low-rank matrix는 연속적인 곱셈을 통해 norm을 더 효율적으로 전파하여, NC의 대안으로서 low-rank 해를 촉진한다. 우리의 주장은 이러한 대안이 softmax code에 해당한다는 것이다. 이는 width-bottlenecked network에서 이전에 발견된 max-margin 해이다. spectral initialization 하에서의 training dynamics를 분석하면서, singular value 사이의 초기 시점 repulsion이 low-rank의 출현을 이끈다는 사실을 밝히고, depth가 NC의 basin of attraction을 어떻게 축소하는지 특성화한다. 마지막으로, 일부 효과는 반대 방향으로 작용함을 보인다. 즉, 무작위로 초기화된 network에서는 width를 증가시키면 학습이 더 높은 rank의 해로 편향된다. 우리의 결과는 정규화되지 않은 multiclass cross-entropy로 학습된 deep UFM에서 implicit bias에 대한 최초의 점근적 및 동역학적 특성화를 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"61607","en":"Sampled hard labels from sparse targets mislead rotation invariant algorithms","ko":"Sparse Target에서 샘플링한 Hard Label은 Rotation Invariant Algorithms를 오도한다","authors":"Avrajit Ghosh, Bin Yu, Manfred Warmuth, Peter Bartlett","pos":"#4514","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=oVt5ioGXPg","abs":"One of the most common machine learning setups is logistic regression. In many classification models, including neural networks, the final prediction is obtained by applying a logistic link function to a linear score. In binary logistic regression, the feedback can be either soft labels, corresponding to the true conditional probability of the data (as in distillation), or sampled hard labels (taking values $\\pm 1$). We point out a fundamental problem that arises even in a particularly favorable setting, where the goal is to learn a noise-free soft target of the form $\\sigma(\\mathbf{x}^{\\top}\\mathbf{w}^{\\star})$. In the over-constrained case (i.e. the number of samples $n$ exceeds the input dimension $d$) with examples  $(\\mathbf{x}_i,\\sigma(\\mathbf{x}_i^{\\top}\\mathbf{w}^{\\star}))$, it is sufficient to recover $\\mathbf{w}^{\\star}$ and hence achieve the Bayes  risk. However, we prove that when the examples are labeled by hard labels $y_i$ sampled from the same conditional distribution $\\sigma(\\mathbf{x}_i^{\\top}\\mathbf{w}^{\\star})$ and $\\mathbf{w}^{\\star}$ is $s$-sparse, then rotation-invariant algorithms are provably suboptimal: they incur an excess risk $\\Omega\\left(\\frac{d-1}{n}\\right)$, while there are simple non-rotation invariant algorithms with excess risk $O(\\frac{s\\log d}{n})$. The simplest rotation invariant algorithm is gradient descent on the logistic loss (with early stopping). A simple non-rotation-invariant algorithm for sparse targets that achieves the above upper bounds uses gradient descent on the weights $u_i,v_i$, where now the linear weight $w_i$ is reparameterized as $u_iv_i$. We conclude that rotation-invariant algorithms cannot efficiently learn noise-free sparse targets from hard labels.","absKo":"가장 흔한 machine learning 설정 중 하나는 logistic regression이다. neural network를 포함한 많은 분류 모델에서 최종 예측은 linear score에 logistic link function을 적용하여 얻어진다. binary logistic regression에서 feedback은 distillation에서처럼 데이터의 true conditional probability에 해당하는 soft label일 수도 있고, 샘플링된 hard label($\\pm 1$ 값을 가짐)일 수도 있다. 우리는 특히 유리한 설정에서도 발생하는 근본적 문제를 지적한다. 즉, 노이즈가 없는 soft target $\\sigma(\\mathbf{x}^{\\top}\\mathbf{w}^{\\star})$를 학습하는 것이 목표인 경우다. over-constrained case(즉, sample 수 $n$이 입력 차원 $d$를 초과하는 경우)에서 예시 $(\\mathbf{x}_i,\\sigma(\\mathbf{x}_i^{\\top}\\mathbf{w}^{\\star}))$가 주어지면, $\\mathbf{w}^{\\star}$를 복원하는 것만으로 Bayes risk에 도달할 수 있다. 그러나 동일한 conditional distribution $\\sigma(\\mathbf{x}_i^{\\top}\\mathbf{w}^{\\star})$로부터 샘플링된 hard label $y_i$로 예시가 주어지고 $\\mathbf{w}^{\\star}$가 $s$-sparse일 때, rotation-invariant algorithm은 증명 가능하게 suboptimal임을 보인다. 이들은 excess risk $\\Omega\\left(\\frac{d-1}{n}\\right)$를 부담하는 반면, 더 단순한 non-rotation invariant algorithm은 excess risk $O\\left(\\frac{s\\log d}{n}\\right)$를 달성한다. 가장 단순한 rotation invariant algorithm은 logistic loss에 대한 gradient descent(early stopping 포함)이다. 위 상한을 달성하는 sparse target용 단순 non-rotation-invariant algorithm은 weight $u_i,v_i$에 대한 gradient descent를 사용하며, 이때 선형 가중치 $w_i$는 $u_iv_i$로 재매개변수화된다. 우리는 rotation-invariant algorithm이 hard label로부터 노이즈 없는 sparse target을 효율적으로 학습할 수 없다고 결론짓는다."},{"id":"65734","en":"Transformers Provably Learn Algorithmic Solutions for Graph Connectivity, But Only with the Right Data","ko":"Transformer는 그래프 연결성에 대한 알고리즘적 해를 증명 가능하게 학습하지만, 올바른 데이터가 있어야만 한다","authors":"Qilin Ye, Deqing Fu, Robin Jia, Vatsal Sharan","pos":"#4600","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=AhRuQzYHzY","abs":"Transformers often fail to learn generalizable algorithms, instead relying on brittle heuristics.  Using graph connectivity as a testbed, we explain this phenomenon both theoretically and empirically. We consider a simplified Transformer architecture, the Disentangled Transformer, and prove that an $L$-layer model can compute connectivity in graphs with diameters up to $3^L$, implementing an algorithm equivalent to computing powers of the adjacency matrix. By analyzing training dynamics, we prove that whether the model learns this strategy hinges on whether most training instances are within this model capacity. Within-capacity graphs (diameter $\\leq 3^L$) drive the learning of the algorithmic solution while beyond-capacity graphs drive the learning of a simple heuristic based on node degrees. Finally, we empirically show that restricting training data to stay within a model's capacity makes both standard and Disentangled Transformers learn the exact algorithm."},{"id":"60792","en":"Dichotomy of Feature Learning and Unlearning: Fast-Slow Analysis on Neural Networks with Stochastic Gradient Descent","ko":"Feature Learning과 Unlearning의 이분법: SGD를 사용하는 Neural Network의 Fast-Slow 분석","authors":"Shota Imai, Sota Nishiyama, Masaaki Imaizumi","pos":"#4607","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=wg02GN1ygj","abs":"<p>The dynamics of gradient-based training in neural networks often exhibit nontrivial structures; hence, understanding them remains a central challenge in theoretical machine learning. In particular, a concept of <em>feature</em> <strong>un</strong><em>learning</em>, in which a neural network progressively loses previously learned features over long training, has gained attention as a way to explain overfitting. In this study, we consider the infinite-width limit of a two-layer neural network updated with a large-batch stochastic gradient, then derive differential equations with different time scales, revealing the mechanism and conditions for feature unlearning to occur. Specifically, we utilize the <em>fast-slow dynamics</em>: while an alignment of first-layer weights develops rapidly, the second-layer weights develop slowly. The direction of a flow on a critical manifold, determined by the slow dynamics, decides whether feature unlearning occurs. We give numerical validation of the result, and derive theoretical grounding and scaling laws of the feature unlearning. Our results yield the following insights: (i) the strength of the primary nonlinear term in data induces the feature unlearning, and (ii) an initial scale of the second-layer weights mitigates the feature unlearning. Technically, our analysis utilizes Tensor Programs and the singular perturbation theory.</p>","absKo":"<p>neural network에서 gradient-based training의 dynamics는 종종 비자명한 구조를 보인다. 따라서 이를 이해하는 일은 이론적 machine learning의 핵심 과제로 남아 있다. 특히, neural network가 긴 training 동안 이전에 학습한 feature를 점진적으로 잃어버리는 <em>feature</em> <strong>un</strong><em>learning</em> 개념은 overfitting을 설명하는 하나의 방식으로 주목받아 왔다. 본 연구에서는 큰 batch stochastic gradient로 업데이트되는 두 층 neural network의 infinite-width limit를 고려한 뒤, 서로 다른 time scale을 갖는 differential equation을 유도하여 feature unlearning이 발생하는 메커니즘과 조건을 밝힌다. 구체적으로, 우리는 <em>fast-slow dynamics</em>를 활용한다. 첫 번째 layer weight의 alignment는 빠르게 형성되는 반면, 두 번째 layer weight는 천천히 형성된다. slow dynamics에 의해 결정되는 critical manifold 위의 flow 방향이 feature unlearning 발생 여부를 결정한다. 우리는 이 결과에 대한 수치적 검증을 제시하고, feature unlearning의 이론적 기반과 scaling law를 유도한다. 우리의 결과는 다음의 통찰을 제공한다: (i) 데이터에서 primary nonlinear term의 세기가 feature unlearning을 유발하고, (ii) second-layer weight의 초기 scale이 feature unlearning을 완화한다. 기술적으로, 우리의 분석은 Tensor Programs와 singular perturbation theory를 활용한다.</p>"},{"id":"60602","en":"Low-dimensional topology of deep neural networks","ko":"딥 신경망의 저차원 위상","authors":"Junyu Ren, Lek-Heng Lim","pos":"#4609","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=yZAbtq7Srt","abs":"We study layered models, including feedforward networks and transformers, by limiting each layer to a width of $d = 3$ neurons, i.e., a representation space of $\\mathbb{R}^3$. This allows us to examine how a neural network changes low-dimensional topological invariants like links and knots, as well as more sophisticated measures like Milnor's $\\mu$-invariant, through the layers. Note that one may simplify or even trivialize just about any topological structure by simply increasing dimension; for example, any knot is equivalent to an unknot in $\\mathbb{R}^4$. By restricting to $\\mathbb{R}^3$, we not only isolate the effects of activation and depth from that of width, we work in a space that lends itself to easy visualization. We provide full mathematical proofs and empirical experiments to justify the following insights: When measured by their power to effect topological changes, ResNets are as powerful as transformers; both are strictly more powerful than feedforward neural networks, which are in turn more powerful than invertible models like flow-based models; but using a non-monotone activation would allow the feedforward networks to become as powerful as ResNets and transformers. These results suggest that low-dimensional topology can be an important tool to guide future designs of AI architectures. We then generalize our results from $d = 3$ to arbitrary $d &gt; 3$.","absKo":"우리는 feedforward network와 transformer를 포함한 layered model을 연구하되, 각 layer를 너비 $d = 3$개의 neuron, 즉 $\\mathbb{R}^3$의 representation space로 제한한다. 이를 통해 신경망이 layer를 거치며 link와 knot 같은 저차원 topological invariant, 그리고 Milnor의 $\\mu$-invariant와 같은 더 정교한 측정을 어떻게 변화시키는지 살펴볼 수 있다. 차원을 단순히 늘리기만 하면 거의 모든 topological structure를 단순화하거나 심지어 trivialize할 수 있다는 점에 유의하라. 예를 들어, 어떤 knot도 $\\mathbb{R}^4$에서는 unknot과 동등하다. $\\mathbb{R}^3$로 제한함으로써 우리는 activation과 depth의 효과를 width의 효과로부터 분리할 뿐 아니라, 시각화가 쉬운 공간에서 작업하게 된다. 우리는 다음 통찰을 정당화하기 위해 완전한 수학적 증명과 실증 실험을 제공한다: topological change를 일으키는 능력으로 측정하면 ResNet은 transformer와 동등하게 강력하며, 둘 다 feedforward neural network보다 엄격히 더 강력하다. 반면 feedforward neural network는 flow-based model과 같은 invertible model보다 더 강력하다. 그러나 non-monotone activation을 사용하면 feedforward network도 ResNet과 transformer만큼 강력해질 수 있다. 이러한 결과는 low-dimensional topology가 향후 AI architecture 설계를 이끄는 데 중요한 도구가 될 수 있음을 시사한다. 이후 우리는 $d = 3$에서 임의의 $d &gt; 3$으로 결과를 일반화한다."},{"id":"68703","en":"Understanding Deep Representation Learning via Layerwise Feature Compression and Discrimination","ko":"Layerwise 특성 압축 및 판별을 통한 심층 표현 학습 이해","authors":"Peng Wang, Xiao Li, Can Yaras, Zhihui Zhu, Laura Balzano, Wei Hu, Qing Qu","pos":"#4610","abs":"<p>Over the past decade, deep learning has proven to be a highly effective tool for learning meaningful features from raw data. However, it remains an open question how deep networks perform hierarchical feature learning across layers. In this work, we attempt to unveil this mystery by investigating the structures of intermediate features. Motivated by our empirical findings that linear layers mimic the roles of deep layers in nonlinear networks for feature learning, we explore how deep linear networks transform input data into output by investigating the output (i.e., features) of each layer after training in the context of multi-class classification problems. Toward this goal, we first define metrics to measure within-class compression and between-class discrimination of intermediate features, respectively. Through theoretical analysis of these two metrics, we show that the evolution of features follows a simple and quantitative pattern from shallow to deep layers when the input data is nearly orthogonal and the network weights are minimum-norm, balanced, and approximately low-rank: each layer of the linear network progressively compresses within-class features at a geometric rate and discriminates between-class features at a linear rate with respect to the number of layers that data have passed through. To the best of our knowledge, this is the first quantitative characterization of feature evolution in hierarchical representations of deep linear networks. Moreover, our extensive experiments not only validate our theoretical results but also reveal a similar pattern in deep nonlinear networks, which aligns well with recent empirical studies. Finally, we demonstrate the practical value of our results in transfer learning.</p>"},{"id":"66539","en":"Why Deep Jacobian Spectra Separate: Depth-Induced Scaling and Singular-Vector Alignment","ko":"심층 Jacobian 스펙트럼이 분리되는 이유: 깊이 유발 스케일링과 특이 벡터 정렬","authors":"Nathanaël Haas, François Gatine, Augustin Cosse, Zied Bouraoui","pos":"#4611","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=2kSBDoP1rE","abs":"<p>Understanding why gradient-based training in deep networks exhibits strong implicit bias remains challenging, in part because tractable singular-value dynamics are typically available only for balanced deep linear models. We propose an alternative route based on two theoretically grounded and empirically testable signatures of deep Jacobians: depth-induced exponential scaling of ordered singular values and strong spectral separation. Adopting a fixed-gates view of piecewise-linear networks, where Jacobians reduce to products of masked linear maps within a single activation region, we prove the existence of Lyapunov exponents governing the top singular values at initialization, give closed-form expressions in a tractable masked model, and quantify finite-depth corrections. We further show that sufficiently strong separation forces singular-vector alignment in matrix products, yielding an approximately shared singular basis for intermediate Jacobians. Together, these results motivate an approximation regime in which singular-value dynamics become effectively decoupled, mirroring classical balanced deep-linear analyses without requiring balancing. Experiments in fixed-gates settings validate the predicted scaling, alignment, and resulting dynamics, supporting a mechanistic account of emergent low-rank Jacobian structure as a driver of implicit bias.</p>"},{"id":"66024","en":"An Algebraic View of the Expressivity of Recurrent Language Models","ko":"순환 언어 모델 표현력의 대수적 관점","authors":"Franz Nowak, Reda Boumasmoud, Ryan Cotterell","pos":"#4613","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=7pbmZatDuD","abs":"<p>Recent progress in language model reasoning capabilities has revived a classic goal: characterizing which algorithms such systems can implement, or equivalently, which formal languages they can recognize. A growing research program studies RNNs, LSTMs, SSMs, and related architectures via reductions to finite-state automata and regular languages. Yet many results are not well-posed: they rely on implicit or incompatible semantic assumptions, invoking associativity and real-arithmetic techniques while also assuming floating-point arithmetic, which is finite and non-associative. Moreover, many proofs are highly architecture-specific and hard to transfer across closely related models. We address these issues with a unifying algebraic framework for a broad class of RNN language models, formally translating them to wreath products of transformation semigroups. By separating universal algebraic structure from contingent choices such as numerical semantics and wiring, the framework yields a disciplined workflow for rigorous expressivity analysis under realistic assumptions. We illustrate its value by rederiving and correcting representative expressivity claims from the literature under explicit deterministic finite-precision semantics.</p>"},{"id":"65802","en":"Magnitude Distance: A Geometric Measure of Dataset Similarity","ko":"Magnitude Distance: 데이터셋 유사도의 기하학적 척도","authors":"Sahel Torkamani, Henry Gouk, Rik Sarkar","pos":"#4614","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=9ylPoHEKed","abs":"Quantifying the distance between datasets is a fundamental question in mathematics and machine learning. We propose \\textit{magnitude distance}, a novel distance metric defined on finite datasets using the notion of the \\emph{magnitude} of a metric space.   The proposed distance incorporates a tunable scaling parameter, $t$, that controls the sensitivity to global structure (small $t$) and finer details (large $t$). We prove several theoretical properties of magnitude distance, including its limiting behavior across scales and conditions under which it satisfies key metric properties.   In contrast to classical distances, we show that magnitude distance remains discriminative in high-dimensional settings when the scale is appropriately tuned.    We further demonstrate how magnitude distance can be used as a training objective for push-forward generative models. Our experimental results support our theoretical analysis and demonstrate that magnitude distance provides meaningful signals, comparable to established distance-based generative approaches."},{"id":"63723","en":"SynGR: Unleashing the Potential of Cross-Modal Synergy for Generative Recommendation","ko":"SynGR: 생성형 추천을 위한 교차 모달 시너지의 잠재력 발휘","authors":"Wei Chen, Xingyu Guo, Shuang Li, Fuwei Zhang, Meng Yuan, Jing Fan, Zhao Zhang, deqing wang, Fuzhen Zhuang","pos":"#1408","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=UGbyWJEI2h","abs":"<p>Generative Recommendation (GR) has emerged as a promising paradigm by formulating item recommendation as a sequence-to-sequence generation task over item identifiers. Recent studies have incorporated multimodal signals to provide richer token-level evidence for generation. However, existing approaches largely rely on alignment- centric fusion and underexplore synergistic information across modalities. In practice, synergistic information plays a critical role in capturing emergent item properties that cannot be inferred from any single modality alone. Such properties encode intrinsic item semantics and guide user preferences, enabling models to move beyond surface-level feature matching. To address this limitation, we propose SynGR, a synergistic generative recommendation framework that explicitly encourages the exploitation of cross-modal dependencies during generation. By constraining overreliance on dominant modalities, SynGR enables the model to capture emergent item semantics beyond shared or modality-specific signals. Extensive experiments across three benchmark datasets demonstrate that SynGR achieves superior recommendation performance, with an average improvement of 9.01%.</p>","absKo":"<p>Generative Recommendation(GR)은 item identifier에 대한 sequence-to-sequence generation task로 item recommendation을 정식화함으로써 유망한 패러다임으로 떠올랐다. 최근 연구들은 더 풍부한 token-level evidence를 생성에 제공하기 위해 multimodal signal을 통합해 왔다. 그러나 기존 접근은 대체로 alignment-centric fusion에 의존하며, modality 간 synergistic information은 충분히 탐구하지 못했다. 실제로 synergistic information은 어떤 단일 modality만으로는 추론할 수 없는 emergent item property를 포착하는 데 중요한 역할을 한다. 이러한 속성은 item의 고유한 semantic을 인코딩하고 user preference를 안내하여, 모델이 표면적인 feature matching을 넘어설 수 있게 한다. 이 한계를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 생성 과정에서 cross-modal dependency의 활용을 명시적으로 장려하는 synergistic generative recommendation framework인 SynGR을 제안한다. SynGR은 지배적인 modality에 대한 과도한 의존을 제한함으로써, shared signal 또는 modality-specific signal을 넘어서는 emergent item semantic을 포착할 수 있게 한다. 세 가지 benchmark dataset에 대한 광범위한 실험은 SynGR이 평균 9.01%의 향상과 함께 더 우수한 recommendation 성능을 달성함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"61462","en":"Causal Representation Learning with Optimal Compression and  Complex Treatments","ko":"최적 압축과 복합 Treatment를 이용한 Causal Representation Learning","authors":"Wanting Liang, Haoang Chi, Zhiheng Zhang","pos":"#206","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=puNfWfBFNT","abs":"Estimating Individual Treatment Effects (ITE) in multi-treatment scenarios faces two critical challenges: the Hyperparameter Selection Dilemma for balancing weights and the Curse of Dimensionality in computational scalability. This paper derives a novel multi-treatment generalization bound and proposes a theoretical estimator for the optimal balancing weight $\\alpha$, eliminating expensive heuristic tuning. We investigate three balancing strategies: Pairwise, One-vs-All (OVA), and Treatment Aggregation. While OVA achieves superior precision in low-dimensional settings, our proposed Treatment Aggregation ensures both accuracy and $\\mathcal{O}(1)$ scalability as the treatment space expands. Furthermore, we extend our framework to a generative architecture, Multi-Treatment CausalEGM, which preserves the Wasserstein geodesic structure of the treatment manifold. Experiments on semi-synthetic and image datasets demonstrate that our approach significantly outperforms traditional models in estimation accuracy and efficiency, particularly in large-scale intervention scenarios.","absKo":"다중 treatment 상황에서 Individual Treatment Effects (ITE)를 추정하는 것은 balancing weights를 위한 Hyperparameter Selection Dilemma와 계산 확장성을 위한 Curse of Dimensionality라는 두 가지 핵심 과제에 직면해 있다. 본 논문은 새로운 multi-treatment generalization bound를 유도하고, 최적 balancing weight $\\alpha$에 대한 이론적 estimator를 제안하여 값비싼 heuristic tuning을 제거한다. 우리는 Pairwise, One-vs-All (OVA), Treatment Aggregation의 세 가지 balancing strategy를 조사한다. OVA는 저차원 설정에서 더 우수한 precision을 보이지만, 우리가 제안하는 Treatment Aggregation은 treatment space가 확장될 때에도 정확도와 $\\mathcal{O}(1)$ scalability를 모두 보장한다. 더 나아가 우리는 이 framework를 generative architecture인 Multi-Treatment CausalEGM으로 확장하며, 이는 treatment manifold의 Wasserstein geodesic structure를 보존한다. semi-synthetic 및 image dataset에서 수행한 실험은, 특히 대규모 intervention 시나리오에서, 우리의 접근법이 추정 정확도와 효율성 측면에서 기존 모델들을 크게 능가함을 보여준다."},{"id":"62125","en":"Causal Identification from Counterfactual Data: Completeness and Bounding Results","ko":"반사실 데이터로부터의 인과 식별: 완전성과 경계 결과","authors":"Arvind Raghavan","pos":"#3403","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=jeCyxur8XB","abs":"<p>Previous work establishing completeness results for <em>counterfactual identification</em> has been limited to the setting where the input data belongs to observational and interventional distributions (Layers 1 and 2 of Pearl's Causal Hierarchy), since it was generally presumed impossible to obtain data from counterfactual distributions, belonging to Layer 3. However, recent work (Raghavan &amp; Bareinboim, 2025) has formally characterized a family of counterfactual distributions which can be directly estimated via experimental methods - a notion they call <em>counterfactual realizabilty</em>. This leaves open the question of what <em>additional</em> Layer 3 quantities now become identifiable, given this new access to (some) Layer 3 data. We develop the <strong>ctfIDu+</strong> algorithm for identifying a counterfactual query from an arbitrary set of Layer 3 data, and prove that it is complete for this task. Using this, we establish the theoretical limit of which counterfactuals can be identified from physically realizable data, thus implying the <em>fundamental limit to exact causal inference in the non-parametric setting</em>. Finally, we derive novel analytic bounds for important non-identifiable quantities given realizable counterfactual data, that are provably tighter than the previously established benchmark. We corroborate using simulations that even if a quantity is non-identifiable, counterfactual data can be used to further tighten bounds for its range.</p>","absKo":"<p><em>counterfactual identification</em>에 대한 completeness result를 확립한 기존 연구는 입력 데이터가 observational 및 interventional distribution(Pearl의 Causal Hierarchy의 Layer 1과 2)에 속하는 경우로 제한되어 왔다. 그 이유는 일반적으로 counterfactual distribution에 해당하는 Layer 3로부터 데이터를 얻는 것이 불가능하다고 여겨졌기 때문이다. 그러나 최근 연구(Raghavan &amp; Bareinboim, 2025)는 실험적 방법으로 직접 추정할 수 있는 일련의 counterfactual distribution을 정식으로 특성화했으며, 이를 그들은 <em>counterfactual realizabilty</em>라고 부른다. 이는 (일부) Layer 3 데이터에 대한 이러한 새로운 접근 권한이 주어졌을 때, 이제 어떤 <em>추가적인</em> Layer 3 quantity가 identifiable해지는지라는 질문을 남긴다. 우리는 임의의 Layer 3 데이터 집합으로부터 counterfactual query를 식별하는 <strong>ctfIDu+</strong> 알고리즘을 개발하고, 이 작업에 대해 complete함을 증명한다. 이를 사용하여, 물리적으로 realizable한 data로부터 어떤 counterfactual이 식별될 수 있는지의 이론적 한계를 확립하며, 이는 <em>non-parametric setting에서 exact causal inference의 근본적 한계</em>를 의미한다. 마지막으로, 우리는 realizable counterfactual data가 주어졌을 때 중요한 non-identifiable quantity에 대한 새로운 analytic bound를 도출하며, 이는 이전에 확립된 benchmark보다 엄밀히 더 타이트함을 증명한다. 시뮬레이션을 통해 어떤 quantity가 identifiable하지 않더라도, counterfactual data를 사용하면 그 범위에 대한 bound를 더 좁힐 수 있음을 확인한다.</p>"},{"id":"65568","en":"Global Directional Priors with Local Statistical Validation for Scalable Causal Discovery","ko":"확장 가능한 인과 발견을 위한 국소 통계 검증 기반 전역 방향 사전정보","authors":"Wei Yuan, Zixuan Shao, Shuhui Wang","pos":"#4006","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=CLgT3XaA2z","abs":"<p>Constraint-based causal discovery relies on conditional independence (CI) tests whose reliability degrades as conditioning sets grow, particularly in hub-dominated graphs. Existing methods constrain adjacency or global structure, but leave conditioning-set dimensionality uncontrolled. In this paper, we propose Ordering-Constrained Markov Blanket discovery (OCMB), a paradigm that treats conditioning-set dimensionality as a first-class constraint. OCMB decouples discovery into two stages: lightweight global ordering estimation providing directional priors, followed by local Markov blanket validation within small, ordering-constrained candidate sets. By enforcing directional constraints before any CI test, OCMB ensures bounded conditioning sets even with hub nodes. We show that OCMB recovers correct parent sets provided a high-recall ordering assumption holds, without requiring the ordering to be globally correct. Experiments demonstrate that OCMB significantly improves precision and robustness over constraint-based and hybrid methods in high-dimensional regimes where conventional CI-based approaches fail.</p>"},{"id":"66381","en":"Linear Causal Representation Learning by Topological Ordering, Pruning, and Disentanglement","ko":"위상 정렬, 가지치기, 분리를 통한 선형 인과 표현 학습","authors":"Hao Chen, Lin Liu, Yu Guang Wang","pos":"#4202","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=4COS6SMf8r","abs":"<p>Causal representation learning (CRL) has garnered increasing interests from the causal inference and artificial intelligence community, due to its capability of disentangling potentially complex data-generating mechanism into causally interpretable latent features, by leveraging the heterogeneity of modern datasets. In this paper, we further contribute to the CRL literature, by focusing on the stylized linear structural causal model over the latent features and assuming a linear mixing function that maps latent features to the observed data or measurements. Existing linear CRL methods often rely on stringent assumptions, such as accessibility to single-node interventional data or restrictive distributional constraints on latent features and exogenous measurement noise. However, these prerequisites can be challenging to satisfy in certain scenarios. In this work, we propose a novel linear CRL algorithm that, unlike most existing linear CRL methods, operates under weaker assumptions about environment heterogeneity and data-generating distributions while still recovering latent causal features up to an equivalence class. We further validate our new algorithm via synthetic experiments and an interpretability analysis of large language models (LLMs), demonstrating both its superiority over competing methods in finite samples and its potential in integrating causality into AI. Source code is available at \\href{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/creator-883D/}{the anonymous link}.</p>"},{"id":"64689","en":"Test-Time Learning of Causal Structure from Interventional Data","ko":"Interventional 데이터로부터 Causal Structure의 Test-Time 학습","authors":"Wei Chen, Rui Ding, Huang Bojun, Yuxuan Liang, Yang Zhang, Qiang Fu, Shi Han, Dongmei Zhang","pos":"#4213","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Kmv7TjGCru","abs":"<p>Supervised Causal Learning has shown promise in causal discovery, yet it often struggles with generalization across diverse interventional settings, particularly when intervention targets are unknown. To address this, we propose TICL (Test-time Interventional Causal  Learning), a novel method that synergizes Test-Time Training with Joint Causal Inference (JCI). Specifically, we design a self-augmentation strategy to generate instance-specific training data at test time, effectively avoiding distribution shifts. Furthermore, by integrating JCI, we developed a PC-inspired two-phase supervised learning scheme, which effectively leverages self-augmented data while ensuring theoretical identifiability. Extensive experiments on bnlearn benchmarks demonstrate TICL's superiority in multiple aspects of causal discovery and intervention target detection.</p>","absKo":"<p>Supervised Causal Learning은 causal discovery에서 유망한 성과를 보여 왔지만, 특히 intervention target이 알려지지 않은 경우 다양한 intervention setting 전반에서의 generalization에 어려움을 겪는 경우가 많다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 Test-Time Training과 Joint Causal Inference (JCI)를 결합한 새로운 방법인 TICL (Test-time Interventional Causal Learning)을 제안한다. 구체적으로, 우리는 test time에 instance-specific training data를 생성하는 self-augmentation strategy를 설계하여 distribution shift를 효과적으로 회피한다. 더 나아가 JCI를 통합함으로써, 우리는 PC-inspired two-phase supervised learning scheme을 개발했으며, 이는 self-augmented data를 효과적으로 활용하는 동시에 이론적 identifiability를 보장한다. bnlearn benchmark에 대한 광범위한 실험은 causal discovery와 intervention target detection의 여러 측면에서 TICL의 우수성을 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"66497","en":"Towards a Holistic Understanding of Selection Bias for Causal Effect Identification","ko":"인과 효과 식별을 위한 선택 편향의 총체적 이해를 향하여","authors":"Yiwen (Evie) Qiu, Filip Kovačević, Shimeng Huang, Peter Spirtes, Francesco Locatello","pos":"#4314","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=39650lCGDP","abs":"<p>Selection bias is pervasive in observational studies. For example, large scale biobanks data can exhibit ``healthy volunteer bias'' when respondents are healthier and of higher socio-economic status than the population they are meant to represent. Recovering causal effects from such sub-population is an important problem in causal inference, as estimating average treatment effects (ATE)  from selected populations can result in a severely biased estimate of the  ATE from the whole population.  In this paper, we investigate the identifiability of the ATE under selection bias. We provide <em>necessary and sufficient conditions</em> for ATE identifiability, leveraging weak assumptions on probability classes to characterize propensity score and selection probability. Compared to previous works, our results extend existing graphical identifiability criteria and offer a more comprehensive understanding of causal effect identification <em>with strictly weaker conditions</em> in the presence of selection bias.</p>"},{"id":"62772","en":"Towards Completeness in Causal Discovery from Soft Interventions with Known Targets","ko":"알려진 Target을 가진 Soft Interventions에서 인과 발견의 Completeness 달성","authors":"Zihan Zhou, Murat Kocaoglu","pos":"#4315","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=dVfJSLGTYm","abs":"We study causal discovery from  soft interventions in the presence of latent confounding. Beyond within-environment conditional independences, soft interventions induce cross-environment invariances that can be encoded using an augmented graph with intervention indicator nodes ($\\mathcal{I}$-AUG). Taking its maximal ancestral graph (MAG) yields the $\\mathcal{I}$-MAG, which characterizes the interventional Markov equivalence class. Building on this framework, we show that the FCI-inspired learner ($\\mathcal{I}$-FCI) by Kocaoglu et al. (2019) is sound but not complete: it may output circle endpoints that are nevertheless compelled by the interventional equivalence class. To exploit intervention-node semantics, we propose two complementary methods. First, we introduce an enumeration-based completion procedure that is sound and theoretically complete, but whose worst-case cost depends on the number of MAGs compatible with the partial graph learned by $\\mathcal{I}$-FCI. Second, we derive a set of additional local orientation rules that provably tighten $\\mathcal{I}$-FCI without increasing asymptotic complexity. Both methods  refine prior outputs in the controlled soft-intervention setting with latent variables.","absKo":"latent confounding이 존재하는 상황에서 soft intervention으로부터 causal discovery를 연구한다. 환경 내부의 conditional independence를 넘어서, soft intervention은 environment 간 invariance를 유도하며, 이는 intervention indicator node ($\\mathcal{I}$-AUG)를 포함하는 augmented graph로 표현될 수 있다. 여기에 maximal ancestral graph (MAG)를 취하면 $\\mathcal{I}$-MAG가 되며, 이는 interventional Markov equivalence class를 특징짓는다. 이 framework를 바탕으로, 우리는 Kocaoglu et al. (2019)의 FCI-inspired learner ($\\mathcal{I}$-FCI)이 sound하지만 complete하지 않음을 보인다. 즉, interventional equivalence class에 의해 사실상 강제되는 circle endpoint를 출력할 수 있다. intervention node semantics를 활용하기 위해, 우리는 서로 보완적인 두 가지 방법을 제안한다. 첫째, enumeration-based completion procedure를 도입하는데, 이는 sound하고 이론적으로 complete하지만 worst-case cost가 $\\mathcal{I}$-FCI가 학습한 partial graph와 양립 가능한 MAG의 수에 의존한다. 둘째, asymptotic complexity를 증가시키지 않으면서 $\\mathcal{I}$-FCI를 이론적으로 더 타이트하게 만드는 추가 local orientation rule 집합을 유도한다. 두 방법 모두 latent variable이 있는 제어된 soft-intervention setting에서 기존 출력을 정제한다."},{"id":"60698","en":"TRACE: Trajectory Recovery for Continuous Mechanism Evolution in Causal Representation Learning","ko":"TRACE: Causal Representation Learning에서 연속적 Mechanism Evolution을 위한 Trajectory Recovery","authors":"Shicheng Fan, Kun Zhang, Lu Cheng","pos":"#4316","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=xRN1Ym2hoa","abs":"<p>Temporal causal representation learning methods assume that causal mechanisms switch instantaneously between discrete domains, yet real-world systems often exhibit <em>continuous</em> mechanism transitions. For example, a vehicle's dynamics evolve gradually through a turning maneuver, and human gait shifts smoothly from walking to running. We formalize this setting by modeling transitional mechanisms as convex combinations of finitely many <em>atomic mechanisms</em>, governed by time-varying mixing coefficients. Our theoretical contributions establish that both the latent causal variables and the continuous mixing trajectory are jointly identifiable. We further propose <strong>TRACE</strong>, a Mixture-of-Experts framework where each expert learns one atomic mechanism during training, enabling recovery of mechanism trajectories at test time. This formulation generalizes to intermediate mechanism states never observed during training. Experiments on synthetic and real-world data demonstrate that TRACE recovers mixing trajectories with up to 0.99 correlation, substantially outperforming discrete-switching baselines.</p>","absKo":"Temporal causal representation learning 방법들은 causal mechanism이 discrete domain 사이에서 즉각적으로 전환된다고 가정하지만, 실제 시스템은 종종 <em>continuous</em> mechanism transition을 보인다. 예를 들어, 차량의 dynamics는 회전 동작을 거치며 점진적으로 변화하고, 인간의 gait는 걷기에서 달리기로 부드럽게 전환된다. 우리는 시간에 따라 변하는 mixing coefficient에 의해 지배되는, 유한 개의 <em>atomic mechanism</em>의 convex combination으로 transitional mechanism을 모델링함으로써 이 설정을 정식화한다. 우리의 이론적 기여는 latent causal variable과 continuous mixing trajectory가 jointly identifiable함을 확립한다. 또한 우리는 각 expert가 training 동안 하나의 atomic mechanism을 학습하는 Mixture-of-Experts framework인 <strong>TRACE</strong>를 제안하며, 이를 통해 test time에 mechanism trajectory를 복원할 수 있다. 이 formulation은 training 중에는 관측되지 않았던 중간 mechanism state로도 일반화된다. synthetic 및 real-world data에서의 실험은 TRACE가 mixing trajectory를 최대 0.99의 correlation으로 복원하며, discrete-switching baseline을 크게 능가함을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"63729","en":"CauScale: Neural Causal Discovery at Scale","ko":"CauScale: 대규모 Neural Causal Discovery","authors":"Bo Peng, Sirui Chen, Jiaguo Tian, Yu Qiao, Chaochao Lu","pos":"#4403","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=UCoD9hpiJs","abs":"Causal discovery is essential for advancing data-driven fields such as scientific AI and data analysis, yet existing approaches face significant time- and space-efficiency bottlenecks when scaling to large  graphs. To address this challenge, we present CauScale, a neural architecture designed for efficient causal discovery that scales inference to graphs with up to 1000 nodes. CauScale improves time efficiency via a reduction unit that compresses data embeddings and improves space efficiency by adopting tied attention weights to avoid maintaining axis-specific attention maps. To keep high causal discovery accuracy, CauScale adopts a two-stream design: a data stream extracts relational evidence from high-dimensional observations, while a graph stream integrates statistical graph priors and preserves key structural signals. CauScale successfully scales to 500-node graphs during training, where prior work fails due to space limitations. Across testing data with varying graph scales and causal mechanisms, \\sys achieves 99.6\\% mAP on in-distribution data and 84.4\\% on out-of-distribution data, while delivering 4$\\times$–13,000$\\times$ inference speedups over prior methods.","absKo":"Causal discovery는 scientific AI와 data analysis 같은 data-driven 분야를 발전시키는 데 필수적이지만, 기존 접근법은 대규모 graph로 확장할 때 심각한 시간 및 공간 효율성 병목에 직면한다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 최대 1000개 node의 graph까지 inference를 확장할 수 있는 효율적인 causal discovery용 neural architecture인 CauScale을 제시한다. CauScale은 data embedding을 압축하는 reduction unit을 통해 시간 효율성을 높이고, 축별 attention map을 유지할 필요가 없도록 tied attention weight를 채택해 공간 효율성을 개선한다. 높은 causal discovery 정확도를 유지하기 위해, CauScale은 two-stream design을 채택한다. data stream은 고차원 관측에서 relational evidence를 추출하고, graph stream은 statistical graph prior를 통합하며 핵심 구조 신호를 보존한다. CauScale은 학습 단계에서 prior work가 공간 제한으로 실패하는 500-node graph까지 성공적으로 확장된다. 다양한 graph scale과 causal mechanism을 가진 test data 전반에서, \\sys는 in-distribution data에서 99.6\\% mAP, out-of-distribution data에서 84.4\\%를 달성하는 동시에, 기존 method 대비 4$\\times$–13,000$\\times$의 inference speedup을 제공한다."},{"id":"60649","en":"Causal Discovery for Irregularly Time Series with Consistency Guarantees","ko":"일관성 보장을 갖춘 불규칙 시계열의 Causal Discovery","authors":"Weihong Li, Baohong Li, Anpeng Wu, Zhihan Li, Ming Ma, Kun Kuang, Keting Yin","pos":"#4404","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=y5GiPedJPV","abs":"<p>This paper studies causal discovery in irregularly sampled time series—a key challenge in risk-sensitive domains like finance, healthcare, and climate science, where missing data and inconsistent sampling frequencies distort causal mechanisms. The main challenge comes from the interdependence between missing data imputation and causal structure recovery: errors in imputation and structure learning can reinforce each other, leading to an inaccurate causal graph. Existing methods either impute first and then discover, or jointly optimize both via neural representation learning, but lack explicit mechanisms to ensure mutual consistency of imputation and structure learning. We address this challenge with ReTimeCausal, an EM-based framework that alternates between imputation and structure learning, which encourages structural consistency throughout the optimization process. Our framework provides theoretical consistency guarantees for structure recovery and extends classical results to settings with irregular sampling and high missingness. ReTimeCausal combines kernel-based sparse regression and structural constraints in an alternating process that updates the completed data and the causal graph in turn. Experiments on synthetic and real-world datasets show that ReTimeCausal is more effective than existing methods under challenging irregular sampling and missing time series data.</p>","absKo":"본 논문은 irregularly sampled time series에서의 causal discovery를 다룬다. 이는 finance, healthcare, climate science와 같이 risk-sensitive한 영역에서 missing data와 불규칙한 sampling frequency가 causal mechanism을 왜곡하기 때문에 핵심적인 도전 과제이다. 주요 어려움은 missing data imputation과 causal structure recovery 사이의 상호의존성에서 비롯된다. 즉, imputation과 structure learning의 오류가 서로를 강화하여 부정확한 causal graph로 이어질 수 있다. 기존 방법은 먼저 impute한 뒤 discovery를 수행하거나, neural representation learning을 통해 둘을 jointly optimize하지만, imputation과 structure learning의 mutual consistency를 보장하는 명시적 메커니즘이 부족하다. 우리는 이 문제를 ReTimeCausal로 해결한다. ReTimeCausal은 imputation과 structure learning을 번갈아 수행하는 EM-based framework로, 최적화 과정 전반에서 structural consistency를 유도한다. 우리의 framework는 structure recovery에 대한 이론적 consistency 보장을 제공하며, irregular sampling과 높은 missingness가 있는 설정으로 고전적 결과를 확장한다. ReTimeCausal은 kernel-based sparse regression과 structural constraints를 번갈아 갱신하는 과정에서 결합하여 completed data와 causal graph를 순차적으로 업데이트한다. synthetic 및 real-world 데이터셋에서의 실험은 ReTimeCausal이 까다로운 irregular sampling과 missing time series data 조건에서 기존 방법들보다 더 효과적임을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"65942","en":"Causal Effect Identifiability in the Presence of Latent Confounders Without Auxiliary Variables","ko":"보조 변수 없이 잠재 교란 요인이 존재할 때의 인과 효과 식별 가능성","authors":"Xiu-Chuan Li, James Kwok, Jiaxian Guo, Tongliang Liu","pos":"#4405","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=8ewf5I4shW","abs":"<p>It is a fundamental challenge to ascertain whether the causal effect of a treatment on an outcome is identifiable in the presence of latent confounders, which serves as the logical prerequisite for recovering the causal effect in a partially observed system. While prior literature demonstrates that the causal effect is identifiable when there exist auxiliary variables subject to stringent structural constraints, this paper investigates identifiability of the causal effect without such variables. This means that we ground identifiability solely in the joint distribution of the treatment-outcome pair, which constitutes the irreducible statistical basis for causal effect identification. Focusing on linear structural causal models (SCMs), we provide a nuanced and complete characterization of identifiability of the causal effect contingent on the distributional properties of exogenous noises. Specifically, we formulate a set of mutually exclusive and collectively exhaustive conditions regarding the Gaussianity of exogenous noises, ascertain under which conditions the causal effect is identifiable and under which it is not, while also quantifying the cardinality of the feasible solution set for the unidentifiable cases. Finally, we empirically validate our theoretical findings.</p>"},{"id":"62929","en":"Dissecting Causal Mechanism Shifts via FANS: Function And Noise Separation","ko":"FANS를 통한 인과 메커니즘 변화 해부: Function and Noise Separation","authors":"Gyeongdeok Seo, Jaeyoon Shim, Mingyu Kim, Hoyoon Byun, Yonghan Jung, Kyungwoo Song","pos":"#4406","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=blowNYT1qn","abs":"<p>Identifying the drivers of causal mechanism shifts, distinguishing functional changes from noise alterations, known as dissection, is a critical yet under-explored problem in data science (e.g., biomedical science and manufacturing). This paper introduces a more general and unified framework, the function and noise separation framework (FANS), that detects and dissects shifts in non-additive, non-linear Structural Causal Models (SCMs) beyond existing additive noise models. Our approach is grounded in a theoretical independence criterion, where function shifts induce a statistical dependence between a node's parents and residual noise. Building on this foundation, we develop a practical two-stage algorithm to efficiently detect and dissect these shifts without retraining. Furthermore, we address the complex challenge of simultaneous function and noise shifts, introducing a formal assumption to resolve their inherent non-identifiability. Our results are corroborated by simulations. Our code is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/FANS-CFEB/.</p>","absKo":"인과 메커니즘 변화의 원인을 식별하고, dissection으로 알려진 기능적 변화와 noise 변화의 구분을 수행하는 것은 data science(예: biomedical science 및 manufacturing)에서 중요하지만 충분히 탐구되지 않은 문제다. 본 논문은 기존 additive noise model을 넘어 non-additive, non-linear Structural Causal Model (SCM)에서의 shift를 탐지하고 dissect하는 더 일반적이고 통합된 framework인 function and noise separation framework (FANS)를 소개한다. 우리의 접근은 이론적 independence criterion에 기반하며, function shift는 node의 parent와 residual noise 사이에 통계적 의존성을 유발한다. 이러한 기반 위에서, 우리는 retraining 없이 이러한 shift를 효율적으로 탐지하고 dissect하는 실용적인 two-stage algorithm을 개발한다. 더 나아가 function shift와 noise shift가 동시에 발생하는 복잡한 문제를 다루기 위해, 그 본질적 비식별성을 해소하는 formal assumption을 도입한다. 우리의 결과는 simulation으로 뒷받침된다. 코드는 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/FANS-CFEB/ 에서 제공된다.</p>"},{"id":"61548","en":"Frequentist Consistency of Prior-Data Fitted Networks for Causal Estimation","ko":"Causal Estimation을 위한 Prior-Data Fitted Networks의 Frequentist Consistency","authors":"Valentyn Melnychuk, Vahid Balazadeh, Stefan Feuerriegel, Rahul G. Krishnan","pos":"#4407","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=p1GwEz0pix","abs":"<p>Foundation models based on prior-data fitted networks (PFNs) have shown strong empirical performance in causal inference by framing it as an in-context learning problem. However, it is unclear whether PFN-based causal estimators provide uncertainty quantification that is consistent with classical frequentist estimators. In this work, we address this gap by analyzing the frequentist consistency of PFN-based estimators for the average treatment effect (ATE). (1) We show that existing PFNs, when interpreted as Bayesian ATE estimators, can exhibit prior-induced confounding bias: the prior is not asymptotically overwritten by data, which, in turn, prevents frequentist consistency. (2) As a remedy, we suggest employing a calibration procedure based on a one-step posterior correction (OSPC). We show that the OSPC helps to restore frequentist consistency and can yield a semi-parametric Bernstein–von Mises theorem for calibrated PFNs (i.e., both the calibrated PFNs and the classical semi-parametric efficient estimators converge with growing data size). (3) Finally, we implement OSPC through tailoring martingale posteriors on top of the PFNs. In this way, we are able to recover nuisance-function posterior distributions from PFNs, required by the OSPC. In multiple (semi-)synthetic experiments, PFNs calibrated with our martingale posterior OSPC produce ATE uncertainty that (i) asymptotically matches frequentist uncertainty and (ii) is often best calibrated in finite samples among other Bayesian ATE estimators.</p>","absKo":"<p>prior-data fitted networks (PFNs)에 기반한 foundation model은 causal inference를 in-context learning 문제로 정식화함으로써 강력한 경험적 성능을 보여왔다. 그러나 PFN-based causal estimator가 classical frequentist estimator와 일관된 uncertainty quantification을 제공하는지는 명확하지 않다. 본 연구에서는 average treatment effect (ATE)에 대한 PFN-based estimator의 frequentist consistency를 분석함으로써 이 격차를 해소한다. (1) 기존 PFN을 Bayesian ATE estimator로 해석할 때 prior-induced confounding bias가 발생할 수 있음을 보인다. 즉, prior가 점근적으로 data에 의해 덮어쓰여지지 않으며, 이는 곧 frequentist consistency를 방해한다. (2) 이에 대한 해결책으로 one-step posterior correction (OSPC)에 기반한 calibration procedure를 제안한다. 우리는 OSPC가 frequentist consistency를 회복하는 데 도움을 주며, calibrated PFN에 대해 semi-parametric Bernstein–von Mises theorem을 도출할 수 있음을 보인다. 즉, calibrated PFN과 classical semi-parametric efficient estimator가 모두 data size가 증가함에 따라 수렴한다. (3) 마지막으로, PFN 위에 martingale posterior를 조정하여 OSPC를 구현한다. 이러한 방식으로 OSPC에 필요한 nuisance-function posterior distribution을 PFN에서 복원할 수 있다. 여러 (semi-)synthetic experiment에서, 우리의 martingale posterior OSPC로 calibration한 PFN은 ATE uncertainty 측면에서 (i) 점근적으로 frequentist uncertainty와 일치하고, (ii) 다른 Bayesian ATE estimator들보다 유한 표본에서 종종 가장 잘 보정된 성능을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"66624","en":"Hierarchical Causal Abduction: A Foundation Framework for Explainable Model Predictive Control","ko":"계층적 인과 귀추: 설명 가능한 Model Predictive Control을 위한 기초 프레임워크","authors":"Ramesh Arvind Naagarajan, Zühal Wagner, Stefan Streif","pos":"#4408","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=22XF7II0Hd","abs":"<p>Model Predictive Control (MPC) is widely used to operate safety-critical infrastructure by predicting future trajectories and optimizing control actions. However, nonlinear dynamics, hard safety constraints, and numerical optimization often render individual control moves opaque to human operators, undermining trust and hindering deployment. This paper presents Hierarchical Causal Abduction (HCA), which combines (i) physics-informed reasoning via domain knowledge graphs, (ii) optimization evidence from Karush--Kuhn--Tucker (KKT) multipliers, and (iii) temporal causal discovery via the PCMCI algorithm to generate faithful, human-interpretable explanations for control actions computed by nonlinear MPC. Across three diverse control applications (greenhouse climate, building HVAC, chemical process engineering) with expert validation, HCA improves explanation accuracy by 53\\% over LIME (0.478 vs. 0.311) using a single set of cross-domain parameters without per-domain tuning; domain-specific KKT-threshold calibration over 2--3 days further increases accuracy to 0.88. Ablation studies confirm that each evidence source is essential, with 32--37\\% accuracy degradation when any component is removed, and HCA's ranking-and-validation methodology generalizes beyond MPC to other prediction-based decision systems, including learning-based control and trajectory planning.</p>"},{"id":"64751","en":"Identifying Partially Observed Causal Models from Heterogeneous/Nonstationary Data","ko":"이질적/비정상 데이터로부터 부분 관측 Causal Model 식별","authors":"Xinshuai Dong, Haoyue Dai, Ignavier Ng, Peter Spirtes, Kun Zhang","pos":"#4409","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=KDDI2gDadL","abs":"<p>Estimating causal structure in the presence of latent variables is an important yet challenging problem. Recent works have shown that distributional constraints, such as rank deficiency constraints of the covariance matrices, can be exploited to recover the underlying causal structure involving latent variables. However, real-world data often exhibit heterogeneity/nonstationarity, which pose challenges to existing methods. In this work, we develop a principled approach for identifying the structure of partially observed linear causal models from heterogenous/nonstationary data. We first formulate a class of heterogenous/nonstationary, partially observed linear causal models and prove that their distributional constraints are equivalent to those in the homogeneous case. Building on this, we propose a novel rank deficiency test that can efficiently handle heterogenous/nonstationary data, and further establish identifiability results for recovering the causal structure involving latent variables. We also provide a method to identify which variables exhibit distribution shifts, i.e., whose causal mechanisms vary across domains. Experiments on simulated and real-world data validate our theoretical findings and the effectiveness of our method.</p>","absKo":"<p>잠재 변수가 존재하는 상황에서 causal structure를 추정하는 것은 중요하지만 어려운 문제다. 최근 연구들은 covariance matrix의 rank deficiency constraint와 같은 distributional constraint를 활용해 잠재 변수가 포함된 underlying causal structure를 복원할 수 있음을 보였다. 그러나 실제 데이터는 종종 heterogeneity/nonstationarity를 보이며, 이는 기존 방법들에 도전이 된다. 본 연구에서는 heterogenous/nonstationary 데이터로부터 partially observed linear causal model의 구조를 식별하기 위한 원리적인 접근법을 개발한다. 먼저 heterogenous/nonstationary한 partially observed linear causal model의 한 클래스를 정식화하고, 이들의 distributional constraint가 homogeneous case의 것과 동치임을 증명한다. 이를 바탕으로, heterogenous/nonstationary 데이터를 효율적으로 처리할 수 있는 새로운 rank deficiency test를 제안하고, 더 나아가 latent variable이 포함된 causal structure를 복원하기 위한 identifiability 결과를 확립한다. 또한 어떤 변수들이 distribution shift를 보이는지, 즉 domains에 따라 causal mechanism이 달라지는지 식별하는 방법도 제시한다. 시뮬레이션 및 실제 데이터 실험은 우리의 이론적 결과와 방법의 효과를 검증한다.</p>"},{"id":"64535","en":"Learning General Causal Structures with Hidden Dynamic Process for Climate Analysis","ko":"기후 분석을 위한 숨겨진 동적 과정을 갖는 일반 인과 구조 학습","authors":"Minghao Fu, Biwei Huang, Zijian Li, Yujia Zheng, Ignavier Ng, Guangyi Chen, Yingyao Hu, Kun Zhang","pos":"#4410","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=MZxhwFT7yF","abs":"<p>Understanding climate dynamics requires going beyond correlations in observational data to uncover their underlying causal process. Latent drivers, such as atmospheric processes, play a critical role in temporal dynamics, while direct causal influences also exist among geographically proximate observed variables. Traditional Causal Representation Learning (CRL) typically focuses on latent factors but overlooks such observable-to-observable causal relations, limiting its applicability to climate analysis. In this paper, we introduce a unified framework that jointly uncovers (i) causal relations among observed variables and (ii) latent driving forces together with their interactions. We establish conditions under which both the hidden dynamic processes and the causal structure among observed variables are simultaneously identifiable from time-series data. Remarkably, our guarantees hold even in the nonparametric setting, leveraging contextual information to recover latent variables and observable relations. Building on these insights, we propose CaDRe (Causal Discovery and Representation learning), a time-series generative model with structural constraints that integrates CRL and causal discovery. Experiments on synthetic datasets validate our theoretical results. On real-world climate datasets, CaDRe not only delivers competitive forecasting accuracy but also recovers visualized causal graphs aligned with domain expertise, thereby offering interpretable insights into climate systems.</p>","absKo":"기후 dynamics를 이해하려면 관측 데이터의 상관관계를 넘어 그 underlying causal process를 밝혀내야 한다. 대기 과정과 같은 latent driver는 시계열 dynamics에서 중요한 역할을 하며, 지리적으로 인접한 관측 변수들 사이에도 직접적인 causal influence가 존재한다. 전통적인 Causal Representation Learning (CRL)은 일반적으로 latent factor에 초점을 맞추지만, 이러한 observable-to-observable causal relation은 간과하여 기후 분석에 대한 적용 가능성을 제한한다. 본 논문에서는 (i) 관측 변수 간 causal relation과 (ii) latent driving force 및 그 상호작용을 동시에 밝혀내는 통합 framework를 제안한다. 우리는 time-series data로부터 hidden dynamic process와 관측 변수 간 causal structure를 동시에 식별할 수 있는 조건을 확립한다. 특히 우리의 보장은 비모수(nonparametric) 설정에서도 성립하며, contextual information을 활용하여 latent variable과 관측 관계를 복원한다. 이러한 통찰을 바탕으로 우리는 구조적 제약을 갖는 time-series generative model인 CaDRe(Causal Discovery and Representation learning)를 제안한다. 이는 CRL과 causal discovery를 통합한다. synthetic dataset에서의 실험은 우리의 이론 결과를 검증한다. 실제 기후 데이터셋에서 CaDRe는 경쟁력 있는 forecasting accuracy를 제공할 뿐만 아니라, 도메인 전문가의 지식과 정렬되는 시각화된 causal graph를 복원하여 기후 시스템에 대한 해석 가능한 통찰을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"61404","en":"Local Covariate Selection for Average Causal Effect Estimation without Pretreatment and Causal Sufficiency Assumptions","ko":"Pretreatment 및 Causal Sufficiency 가정 없이 Average Causal Effect Estimation을 위한 Local Covariate Selection","authors":"Zeyu Liu, Zheng Li, Feng Xie, Yan Zeng, Hao Zhang, Kun Zhang","pos":"#4412","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=qZVcGlU5lN","abs":"<p>Causal effect estimation is a fundamental task in many scientific fields. Selecting appropriate covariates for adjustment is crucial for obtaining unbiased causal effects. However, most existing methods either rely on learning the global causal structure, assume the absence of latent variables, or impose the pretreatment assumption-restricts covariates to those unaffected by the treatment or outcome. These assumptions are often unrealistic in real-world scenarios, and global structure learning can be computationally intensive and inefficient. To address these challenges, we first characterize the local existence boundary of adjustment sets for causal effect estimation. Based on this characterization, we develop a novel local learning method for covariate selection in nonparametric causal effect estimation. This method accommodates the presence of latent variables and eliminates the need for the pretreatment assumption. We prove that the proposed method is both sound and complete under standard assumptions. Its effectiveness is validated through extensive experiments on both synthetic and real-world datasets.</p>","absKo":"<p>Causal effect estimation은 많은 과학 분야에서 핵심적인 과제이다. unbiased causal effect를 얻기 위해서는 적절한 covariate를 adjustment에 선택하는 것이 매우 중요하다. 그러나 기존 방법의 대부분은 전역 causal structure 학습에 의존하거나, latent variable의 부재를 가정하거나, 혹은 pretreatment assumption을 부과하는데, 이는 covariate를 treatment나 outcome의 영향을 받지 않은 것들로 제한한다. 이러한 가정은 실제 시나리오에서 종종 비현실적이며, 전역 structure learning은 계산적으로도 매우 비싸고 비효율적일 수 있다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 먼저 causal effect estimation을 위한 adjustment set의 local existence boundary를 특성화한다. 이 특성화에 기반하여, 비모수적 causal effect estimation에서 covariate 선택을 위한 새로운 local learning method를 개발한다. 이 방법은 latent variable의 존재를 허용하며 pretreatment assumption이 필요하지 않다. 우리는 제안한 방법이 표준 가정 하에서 sound하고 complete함을 증명한다. 그 효과는 synthetic 및 real-world dataset에 대한 광범위한 실험을 통해 검증된다.</p>"},{"id":"65660","en":"PACER: Acyclic Causal Discovery from Large-scale Interventional Data","ko":"PACER: 대규모 개입 데이터로부터의 비순환 인과 발견","authors":"Ramon Viñas Torné, Sílvia Fàbregas Salazar, Soyon Park, Ivo Alexander Ban, Artyom Gadetsky, Nikita Doikov, Maria Brbic","pos":"#4414","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=BS8upx3Smw","abs":"<p>Inferring the structure of directed acyclic graphs (DAGs) from data is a central challenge in causal discovery, particularly in modern high-dimensional settings where large-scale interventional data are increasingly available. While interventional data can substantially improve identifiability, existing differentiable causal discovery methods rely on soft acyclicity constraints, leading to optimization over invalid cyclic graphs, numerical instability, and limited scalability. We introduce PACER (Perturbation-driven Acyclic Causal Edge Recovery), a scalable framework for causal discovery that guarantees acyclicity by construction. PACER parameterizes a distribution over DAGs through a joint model of variable permutations and edge probabilities, enabling direct optimization over valid causal structures without surrogate penalties. The framework supports a unified likelihood-based treatment of observational and interventional data, flexible conditional density models, and the incorporation of structural prior knowledge. For linear-Gaussian mechanisms, we derive closed-form expressions for the expected interventional log-likelihood and its gradients, yielding substantial computational gains. Empirically, PACER matches or exceeds state-of-the-art methods on protein signaling and large-scale genetic perturbation benchmarks, while scaling efficiently to networks with thousands of variables and achieving up to two orders of magnitude speedups over penalty-based differentiable approaches. These results demonstrate that exact and scalable causal discovery from high-dimensional perturbation data is achievable through principled search space design.</p>"},{"id":"61300","en":"Partial Identification under High-Dimensional Potential Outcomes and Confounders via  Optimal Transport","ko":"Optimal Transport를 통한 고차원 잠재 결과와 교란변수 하의 부분 식별","authors":"Yunfeng Wang, Zhiheng Zhang, Zijun Gao","pos":"#4415","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=raKcsJbVDY","abs":"<p>Partial identification provides informative causal guarantees when point identification is impossible, but existing approaches based on optimal transport (OT) become computationally and statistically intractable in high-dimensional settings. This limitation is particularly severe when both potential outcomes and confounders are high-dimensional, where classical OT-based bounds suffer from the curse of dimensionality and unfavorable convergence rates. To address this challenge, we propose a novel estimator that decomposes the transport problem into a low-dimensional signal subspace and a high-dimensional residual subspace. Unlike existing projection-based methods that discard residual information, we recover the residual transport energy using the Sliced Wasserstein distance, which is computationally efficient and robust to high dimensions. We establish interpretable conditions controlling the approximation gap based on residual structure and provide a data-driven rule for signal dimension selection. Empirical results show that our estimator consistently outperforms projection-only baselines by recovering lost transport energy, yielding more informative causal bounds while remaining computationally tractable in high dimensions.</p>","absKo":"<p>Partial identification은 point identification이 불가능할 때도 정보성 있는 causal guarantee를 제공하지만, optimal transport (OT)에 기반한 기존 접근법은 고차원 설정에서 계산적으로도 통계적으로도 다루기 어렵습니다. 이러한 한계는 potential outcome과 confounder가 모두 고차원일 때 특히 심각하며, classical OT 기반 bound는 curse of dimensionality와 불리한 convergence rate에 시달립니다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 transport problem을 저차원 signal subspace와 고차원 residual subspace로 분해하는 새로운 estimator를 제안합니다. residual 정보를 버리는 기존 projection-based method와 달리, 우리는 Sliced Wasserstein distance를 사용해 residual transport energy를 복원하며, 이는 계산적으로 효율적이고 고차원에 강건합니다. 우리는 residual structure를 바탕으로 approximation gap을 제어하는 해석 가능한 조건을 정립하고, signal dimension 선택을 위한 데이터 기반 규칙도 제시합니다. 실험 결과, 우리의 estimator는 잃어버린 transport energy를 복원함으로써 projection-only baseline을 일관되게 능가하며, 고차원에서도 계산적으로 다루기 쉬우면서 더 정보성 있는 causal bound를 제공합니다.</p>"},{"id":"61833","en":"Skewness-Robust Causal Discovery in Location-Scale Noise Models","ko":"Location-Scale Noise Model에서 왜도에 강건한 인과 발견","authors":"Daniel Klippert, Alexander Marx","pos":"#4416","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=mXn4ueFKnQ","abs":"To distinguish Markov equivalent graphs in causal discovery, it is necessary to restrict the structural causal model. A flexible class of models that is general and identifiable in most cases are location-scale noise models (LSNMs), in which the effect $Y$ is modeled based on its causes $\\boldsymbol{X}$ as $Y = f(\\boldsymbol{X}) + g(\\boldsymbol{X})N$.    To facilitate the estimation of these models, a prominent assumption is that the noise variable $N$ follows a symmetric distribution.   We show that when $N$ is a skewed random variable,    which is likely in real-world domains, such approaches drop in performance.   To address this limitation, we propose SkewD, a likelihood-based method for causal discovery under LSNMs    with skewed noise, employing a combination of heuristic search and expectation conditional maximization for parameter estimation. SkewD extends the usual normal distribution framework to the skew-normal setting,    enabling reliable inference under symmetric and skewed noise. While our main focus is on bivariate cause-effect inference, we further showcase how SkewD can be extended to the multivariate setting.","absKo":"Causal discovery에서 Markov equivalent graphs를 구별하려면 structural causal model을 제한할 필요가 있다. 일반적이고 대부분의 경우 식별 가능한 유연한 모델 계열은 location-scale noise models (LSNMs)로, 여기서 효과 $Y$는 자신의 원인 $\\boldsymbol{X}$에 기반하여 $Y = f(\\boldsymbol{X}) + g(\\boldsymbol{X})N$으로 모델링된다. 이러한 모델의 추정을 용이하게 하기 위해, 널리 쓰이는 가정은 noise variable $N$이 symmetric distribution을 따른다는 것이다. 우리는 $N$이 skewed random variable일 때, 실제 세계 도메인에서 충분히 가능한 상황인데, 이러한 접근법의 성능이 저하된다는 점을 보인다. 이 한계를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 skewed noise를 갖는 LSNMs 하에서의 causal discovery를 위한 likelihood-based method인 SkewD를 제안한다. SkewD는 parameter estimation을 위해 heuristic search와 expectation conditional maximization의 조합을 사용한다. SkewD는 일반적인 normal distribution framework를 skew-normal setting으로 확장하여, symmetric 및 skewed noise 모두에서 신뢰할 수 있는 inference를 가능하게 한다. 우리의 주된 초점은 bivariate cause-effect inference에 있지만, SkewD가 multivariate setting으로 확장될 수 있음도 추가로 보인다."},{"id":"67168","en":"Position: VLM Causal Reasoning Benchmarks Should Probe Temporal Understanding, Not Presume It","ko":"Position: VLM 인과 추론 벤치마크는 시간적 이해를 전제하지 말고 탐침해야 한다","authors":"Chinh Hoang, Mohammad Hasan","pos":"#2713","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=NmiiK9yQMM","abs":"<p>This position paper argues that vision-language model (VLM) benchmarks for causal reasoning rely on two under-examined assumptions. First, benchmarks presuppose temporal constitution, the understanding of time as the medium through which causes produce effects, without testing it as a prerequisite. Second, they insufficiently distinguish external symbolic scaffolding from internalized capability; scaffolding-invariance is the diagnostic signature of genuine internalization. Drawing on frameworks from art, philosophy, and psychoanalysis, we propose diagnostics that probe these foundations. Preliminary evidence from three VLMs shows systematic disparity between fluent causal text and valid causal structure, and qualitatively different responses to identical scaffolding manipulation. None of these patterns indicates constitutive internalization. Progress requires benchmarks that test temporal understanding and scaffolding-invariance, not only output accuracy.</p>"},{"id":"66542","en":"The Abstraction Gap in Vision-Language Causal Reasoning","ko":"Vision-Language 인과 추론에서의 추상화 격차","authors":"Chinh Hoang, Mohammad Hasan","pos":"#4306","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=2juEZmkLdn","abs":"<p>Vision-language models (VLMs) generate fluent causal explanations for visual scenes, but does this fluency reflect genuine structural understanding? We address this question through a dual-probe methodology that isolates plausibility from faithfulness. The Text-Only Probe measures linguistic quality; the Chain-Text Probe requires models to first generate explicit causal chains before text responses. We define the Abstraction Gap (AG) metric as the normalized performance difference between probes, operationalizing the plausibility-faithfulness distinction from explainable AI research. Applying this methodology to eight VLMs using CAGE (Causal Abstraction Gap Evaluation), a benchmark of 49,500 questions across 5,500 images spanning Pearl's causal hierarchy, we find seven models exhibit AG exceeding 0.50: scoring 6--8 on text but below 2.5 on chains, often producing blank outputs. Fine-tuning on 45,000 chain-annotated examples fails to close the gap, indicating that explicit chain supervision cannot instill structural abstraction capability. Current VLMs optimize for plausible language without faithful structural understanding.</p>"},{"id":"65136","en":"CentaurEval: Benchmarking Human-in-the-Loop Value in Agentic Coding","ko":"CentaurEval: 에이전트 코딩에서 Human-in-the-Loop 가치 벤치마킹","authors":"Hanjun Luo, Chiming Ni, Jiaheng Wen, Zhimu Huang, Bingduo Liao, Yiran Wang, Sylvia Chung Yan Shan, Yingbin Jin, Jialin Li, Xinfeng Li, Wenyuan Xu, XiaoFeng Wang, Hanan Salam","pos":"#3808","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=GR335S9IgZ","abs":"<p>LLM-powered coding agents are reshaping the development paradigm. However, existing evaluation systems, neither traditional tests for humans nor benchmarks for LLMs, fail to capture this shift, excluding problems that require both human reasoning to guide solutions and AI efficiency for implementation. We introduce CentaurEval, a unified, ecologically valid benchmark for measuring human-in-the-loop value in coding. CentaurEval's core innovation is its \"Collaboration-Necessary\" problem templates, which are intractable for standalone LLMs or humans, but solvable through effective collaboration. CentaurEval dynamically instantiates tasks from 45 templates, providing a standardized IDE for humans and a reproducible 450-task toolkit for LLMs. We benchmark 45 participants against 5 LLMs under 4 levels of human intervention. Results show that while LLMs or humans alone achieve poor pass rates (0.67% and 18.89%), human–AI collaboration significantly improves to 31.11%. Our analysis reveals an emerging co-reasoning partnership, challenging the traditional human-tool hierarchy by showing that strategic breakthroughs can originate from either humans or AI. Our work is openly accessible.</p>"},{"id":"60767","en":"The Perception–Physics Paradox: Probing Scientific Alignment with TC-Atlas","ko":"Perception–Physics Paradox: TC-Atlas로 과학적 Alignment 탐색","authors":"Dingling Yao, Andrea Polesello, Adeel Pervez, Caroline Muller, Francesco Locatello","pos":"#2617","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=wqs3uxBFRo","abs":"<p>While Vision Foundation Models (VFMs) excel at predictive tasks on satellite imagery, their performance can arise from visual correlations rather than underlying structural invariants, making certain perception-based out-of-distribution accuracy a poor proxy for scientific utility.  As a result, models may look correct without reasoning correctly—a discrepancy we term the <em>Perception–Physics Paradox</em>.  To address this gap, we introduce <em>Scientific Alignment</em> as an implicit objective for representation learning in scientific domains.  We study a principled, testable aspect of scientific alignment through <em>Structural Isomorphism</em>, which requires latent representations to uniquely identify physical systems up to a linear reparameterization.  This perspective induces a hierarchy of necessary conditions and yields a systematic probing protocol for physical and causal interpretability.  To operationalize this framework, we release <em>TC-Atlas</em>, a foundational global dataset and automated construction pipeline for tropical cyclone research, and show that current VFMs rely on visual shortcuts that collapse in extreme regimes, indicating that scientific alignment does not arise as a natural byproduct of visual scaling alone.</p>","absKo":"<p>Vision Foundation Model (VFM)은 satellite imagery에서의 predictive task에 뛰어나지만, 그 성능은 underlying structural invariant이 아니라 visual correlation에서 비롯될 수 있어, 특정 perception-based out-of-distribution 정확도는 scientific utility의 부정확한 proxy가 된다. 그 결과, 모델은 올바르게 보이지만 올바르게 추론하지 못할 수 있으며, 우리는 이러한 불일치를 <em>Perception–Physics Paradox</em>라고 부른다. 이 간극을 해소하기 위해, 우리는 scientific domain에서 representation learning을 위한 implicit objective로 <em>Scientific Alignment</em>를 제안한다. 우리는 <em>Structural Isomorphism</em>을 통해 scientific alignment의 원칙적이고 검증 가능한 한 측면을 연구하는데, 이는 latent representation이 linear reparameterization까지의 physical system을 유일하게 식별할 것을 요구한다. 이러한 관점은 필요한 조건의 위계를 유도하고, 물리 및 인과 해석 가능성을 위한 체계적인 probing protocol을 제공한다. 이 framework를 실제로 활용하기 위해, 우리는 tropical cyclone 연구를 위한 기초적인 전역 dataset이자 자동 구축 pipeline인 <em>TC-Atlas</em>를 공개하고, 현재의 VFM이 극한 regime에서 붕괴하는 visual shortcut에 의존하고 있음을 보여줌으로써, scientific alignment가 단순한 visual scaling의 자연스러운 부산물로는 나타나지 않음을 밝힌다.</p>"},{"id":"60942","en":"Evidential Copula Concept Embedding Models","ko":"증거적 Copula 개념 임베딩 모델","authors":"Yanjie Qiu, Xiaodong Yue, Xuhui Fan, Yufei Chen, Jie Shi, Wei Liu","pos":"#3201","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=v9rybnvds5","abs":"<p>Concept Embedding Models (CEMs) advance interpretable AI by extending Concept Bottleneck Models (CBMs) through semantic concept embeddings, providing an important solution in high-stakes domains such as medical diagnosis where accuracy and interpretability are critical. However, a fundamental limitation persists: existing CEMs inherently assume concept independence, critically overlooking the highly complex dependencies among concepts. To address this, we propose an Evidential Copula Concept Embedding Model (EC-CEM) that redefines the joint distribution over concepts, capturing inter-concept dependencies while maintaining a flexible structure that decouples the marginal concept distributions from their dependency structure. In particular, EC-CEM relaxes the concept independence assumption and uniquely integrates Copula theory with evidential deep learning to define a joint distribution over concepts. The proposed EC-CEM also develops two training objectives that aim at classification and concept modeling simultaneously. We provide theoretical justification via variational inference and demonstrate empirical superiority through extensive experiments.</p>","absKo":"<p>Concept Embedding Models (CEMs)는 semantic concept embeddings를 통해 Concept Bottleneck Models (CBMs)를 확장함으로써 interpretable AI를 발전시켰으며, 정확성과 해석가능성이 모두 중요한 medical diagnosis와 같은 고위험 도메인에서 중요한 해법을 제공한다. 그러나 근본적인 한계는 여전히 남아 있다. 기존 CEMs는 본질적으로 concept independence를 가정하여, concepts 사이의 매우 복잡한 의존성을 결정적으로 간과한다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 Evidential Copula Concept Embedding Model (EC-CEM)을 제안한다. 이는 concepts에 대한 joint distribution을 재정의하여 inter-concept dependencies를 포착하는 동시에, marginal concept distributions와 dependency structure를 분리하는 유연한 구조를 유지한다. 특히 EC-CEM은 concept independence assumption을 완화하고, Copula theory와 evidential deep learning을 독창적으로 통합하여 concepts에 대한 joint distribution을 정의한다. 제안하는 EC-CEM은 classification과 concept modeling을 동시에 목표로 하는 두 개의 training objective도 개발한다. 우리는 variational inference를 통해 이론적 정당화를 제시하고, 광범위한 실험을 통해 empirical superiority를 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"62560","en":"LassoFlexNet: a Flexible Neural Architecture for Tabular Data","ko":"LassoFlexNet: Tabular Data용 유연한 Neural Architecture","authors":"Kry Yik Chau Lui, Cheng Chi, Kishore Basu, Yanshuai Cao","pos":"#1514","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=fY2cXSIxHO","abs":"<p>Deep neural networks excel in vision, language, and audio, yet continue to underperform relative to tree-based models on tabular data. We identify and extend inductive biases crucial for tabular learning—robustness to irrelevant features, axis alignment, localized irregularities, feature heterogeneity, and training stability—and propose <em>LassoFlexNet</em>, a novel architecture coupled with a new training algorithm. LassoFlexNet employs a Tied Group Lasso mechanism that sparsely selects raw inputs based on nonlinear per-feature embeddings. This design encourages a raw input variable to contribute jointly with others only if it provides marginal predictive value, linearly or nonlinearly. The resulting non-homogeneity and localized irregularities introduce optimization challenges that defeat standard stochastic and proximal-gradient methods. To address this, we develop a <em>Sequential Hierarchical Proximal Gradient optimizer with exponential moving averages (EMA)</em>, enabling stable training. Across 52 datasets from three recent benchmarks, LassoFlexNet matches or surpasses state-of-the-art tree-based models, achieving up to 10% relative gains while improving interpretability. We further validate our design through ablation studies and prove enhanced expressivity for a key architectural component.</p>","absKo":"<p>Deep neural networks는 vision, language, audio에서는 탁월한 성능을 보이지만, tabular data에서는 tree-based models에 비해 여전히 성능이 뒤처진다. 우리는 tabular learning에 중요한 inductive bias들, 즉 irrelevant features에 대한 robustness, axis alignment, localized irregularities, feature heterogeneity, training stability를 식별하고 확장하여, 새로운 training algorithm과 결합된 새로운 architecture인 <em>LassoFlexNet</em>을 제안한다. LassoFlexNet은 non-linear한 per-feature embeddings를 기반으로 raw inputs를 sparse하게 선택하는 Tied Group Lasso 메커니즘을 사용한다. 이 설계는 각 raw input variable이 선형 또는 비선형적으로 marginal predictive value를 제공할 때에만 다른 변수들과 함께 joint하게 기여하도록 유도한다. 그 결과 나타나는 non-homogeneity와 localized irregularities는 표준 stochastic 및 proximal-gradient methods를 무력화하는 optimization challenges를 야기한다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 <em>exponential moving averages (EMA)를 사용하는 Sequential Hierarchical Proximal Gradient optimizer</em>를 개발하여 안정적인 학습을 가능하게 했다. 세 개의 최근 benchmark에서 가져온 52개 데이터셋 전반에서 LassoFlexNet은 state-of-the-art tree-based models와 동등하거나 이를 능가했으며, 해석 가능성을 높이면서 최대 10%의 상대적 성능 향상을 달성했다. 또한 ablation study를 통해 설계를 추가로 검증하고, 핵심 architectural component에 대한 expressivity 향상을 증명한다.</p>"},{"id":"64034","en":"Uncovering the Gradient Geometry of Long CoT: A Spectral-guided Approach to Reasoning Distillation","ko":"긴 CoT의 그래디언트 기하학 규명: 추론 증류를 위한 스펙트럼 기반 접근법","authors":"Sinan Fan, Xiaofeng Sun, Chen Shen, Chenxi Huang, Shaotian Yan, Bing Wang, kaiyuan liu, Xiaosong Yuan, Liang Xie, Wenxiao Wang, Jun Zhang, Hongyang Chen, Jieping Ye","pos":"#1602","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=RXSg2U6R1G","abs":"<p>Large reasoning models (LRMs) achieve remarkable reasoning performance by generating long chains-of-thought (CoT). However, standard supervised fine-tuning (SFT) treats all tokens uniformly, indiscriminately minimizing loss across both essential reasoning steps and those that are noisy, redundant, or instance-specific. This often leads student models to memorize superficial patterns rather than acquire generalizable reasoning capabilities. To better understand this limitation, we introduce \\textit{Loss Subspace Attribution}, a gradient decomposition analysis approach that uncovers a striking geometric structure:  Gradients corresponding to effective reasoning predominantly lie within a low-rank consensus subspace, while conflicting or unstructured signals dominate the residual subspace. Guided by this insight, we propose \\textbf{\\textit{Spectral-guided Learning}}, a step-level distillation strategy that uses spectral strength to identify reasoning steps aligned with the consensus subspace and prioritizes their contribution to parameter updates, while suppressing gradients from the residual subspace. Experiments across various LRMs and diverse complex reasoning tasks consistently demonstrate that focusing optimization on the consensus subspace yields more robust and generalizable student models.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large reasoning model (LRM)은 긴 chain-of-thought (CoT)를 생성함으로써 뛰어난 reasoning 성능을 달성합니다. 그러나 표준 supervised fine-tuning (SFT)은 모든 token을 동일하게 취급하여, 필수적인 reasoning step과 noisy, redundant, 또는 instance-specific한 step 모두에 걸쳐 loss를 무차별적으로 최소화합니다. 이는 student model이 일반화 가능한 reasoning capability를 학습하기보다 표면적인 패턴을 암기하게 만드는 경우가 많습니다. 이러한 한계를 더 잘 이해하기 위해 우리는 강력한 기하학적 구조를 밝혀내는 gradient decomposition analysis 접근법인 \\textit{Loss Subspace Attribution}을 도입합니다: 효과적인 reasoning에 해당하는 gradient는 주로 low-rank consensus subspace에 위치하는 반면, 상충하거나 구조화되지 않은 신호는 residual subspace를 지배합니다. 이 통찰에 따라 우리는 \\textbf{\\textit{Spectral-guided Learning}}을 제안합니다. 이는 spectral strength를 사용해 consensus subspace와 정렬된 reasoning step을 식별하고 parameter update에 대한 기여를 우선시하는 step-level distillation strategy이며, residual subspace의 gradient는 억제합니다. 다양한 LRM과 복잡한 reasoning task 전반의 실험은 consensus subspace에 최적화를 집중할 때 더 robust하고 일반화 가능한 student model이 얻어짐을 일관되게 보여 줍니다.</p>"},{"id":"65668","en":"FairMerging: Rethinking Model Merging through the Lens of Fairness","ko":"FairMerging: 공정성 관점에서 모델 병합 재고하기","authors":"Bing Liu, Xinrui Shan, Boyu Zhang, Qiankun Zhang, Bin Yuan, Wang, Xianjun Deng","pos":"#4004","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=BOeTJbY5Af","abs":"<p><em>Model merging</em> offers an appealing route to multi-task learning by composing independently fine-tuned checkpoints without centralized data or retraining. However, this convenience can come with a hidden cost. Model merging may <em>amplify</em> performance disparities across subgroups, raising fairness concerns even when average accuracy remains competitive. To explain this phenomenon, we develop a sensitivity-based theoretical analysis that upper bounds the fairness gap induced by model merging. Theoretical analysis with empirical verifications reveals that the resulting fairness gap is governed by two coupled factors, a <em>merging magnitude</em> term that measures how far the merged parameters move from the target model and <em>global sensitivity</em> terms that determine how unevenly the perturbation affects subgroup losses. Guided by these insights, we propose <em>FairMerging</em>, a two-stage merging framework that first reduces the sensitivity of the target model and then performs fairness-aware coefficient optimization with orthogonally normalized task vectors. Experiments across multiple datasets, backbones, and merging baselines demonstrate that FairMerging substantially mitigates unfairness while retaining competitive multi-task performance.</p>"},{"id":"66641","en":"Advancing Analytic Class-Incremental Learning through Vision-Language Calibration","ko":"Vision-Language 보정을 통한 해석적 클래스 증분 학습 발전","authors":"Binyu Zhao, Wei ZHANG, Xingrui Yu, Zhaonian Zou, Ivor Tsang","pos":"#4204","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=1sH1AEeylU","abs":"<p>Class-incremental learning (CIL) with pre-trained models (PTMs) faces a critical trade-off between efficient adaptation and long-term stability. While analytic learning enables rapid, recursive closed-form updates, its efficacy is often compromised by accumulated errors and feature incompatibility. In this paper, we first conduct a systematic study to dissect the failure modes of PTM-based analytic CIL, identifying representation rigidity as the primary bottleneck. Motivated by these insights, we propose <strong>VILA</strong>, a novel dual-branch framework that advances analytic CIL via a two-level vision-language calibration strategy. Specifically, we coherently fuse plastic, task-adapted features with a frozen, universal semantic anchor at the feature level through geometric calibration, and leverage cross-modal priors at the decision level to rectify prediction bias. This confluence maintains AL's extreme efficiency while overcoming its inherent brittleness. Extensive experiments across eight benchmarks demonstrate that VILA consistently yields superior performance, particularly in fine-grained and long-sequence scenarios. Our framework harmonizes high-fidelity prediction with the simplicity of analytic learning. Our code will be made publicly available upon acceptance.</p>"},{"id":"65823","en":"Beyond Accuracy and Complexity: The Effective Information Criterion for Structurally Stable Symbolic Regression","ko":"정확도와 복잡도를 넘어서: 구조적으로 안정적인 기호 회귀를 위한 유효 정보 기준","authors":"Zihan Yu, Guanren Wang, Jingtao Ding, Huandong Wang, Yong Li","pos":"#4205","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=9mFx2t9RGj","abs":"Symbolic regression (SR) traditionally balances accuracy and complexity, implicitly assuming that simpler formulas are structurally more rational. We argue that this assumption is insufficient: existing algorithms often exploit this metric to discover accurate and compact but structurally irrational formulas that are numerically ill-conditioned and physically inexplicable. Inspired by the structural stability of real physical laws, we propose the Effective Information Criterion (EIC) to quantify formula rationality. EIC models formulas as information channels and measures the amplification of inherent rounding noise during recursive calculation, effectively distinguishing physically plausible structures from pathological ones without relying on ground truth. Our analysis reveals a stark structural stability gap between human-derived equations and SR-discovered results. By integrating EIC into SR workflows, we provide explicit structural guidance: for heuristic search, EIC steers algorithms toward stable regions to yield superior Pareto frontiers; for generative models, EIC-based filtering improves pre-training sample efficiency by 2–4 times and boosts generalization $R^2$ by 22.4\\%. Finally, an extensive study with 108 human experts shows that EIC aligns with human preferences in 70\\% of cases, validating structural stability as a critical prerequisite for human-perceived interpretability. We release our code at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/EIC-91B2."},{"id":"63153","en":"Beyond Magnitude: Scale-Invariant Evidential Fusion for Multi-View Classification","ko":"크기를 넘어서: 다중 뷰 분류를 위한 스케일 불변 증거 융합","authors":"Wei Liu, Yufei Chen, Jie Shi, Xiaodong Yue","pos":"#4206","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ZZNKx9eZMB","abs":"<p>Evidential Deep Learning (EDL) enables trustworthy multi-view classification, yet suffers from a critical vulnerability: the Scale Mismatch Problem. We theoretically demonstrate that existing evidential fusion rules erroneously equate logit magnitude with semantic confidence, rendering them susceptible to semantic hijacking by inflated but uninformative views. To resolve this, we propose Scale-Invariant Evidential Fusion (SAEF), a framework utilizing instance-wise standardization to strictly decouple confidence from scale. Instead of relying on magnitude dominance, SAEF aggregates views based on statistical consensus. Theoretically, SAEF guarantees invariance to global scaling and robustness to asymmetric dominance. Experiments on four diverse datasets confirm that SAEF outperforms state-of-the-art baselines in accuracy and robustness to semantic conflicts and noise, ensuring stability against severe scale perturbations.</p>","absKo":"<p>Evidential Deep Learning (EDL)은 신뢰할 수 있는 multi-view classification을 가능하게 하지만, Scale Mismatch Problem이라는 치명적인 취약점을 안고 있다. 우리는 기존 evidential fusion rule이 logit magnitude를 semantic confidence와 잘못 동일시함으로써, 값만 커지고 정보는 없는 view에 의한 semantic hijacking에 취약해짐을 이론적으로 보인다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 instance-wise standardization을 활용하여 confidence와 scale을 엄격히 분리하는 Scale-Invariant Evidential Fusion (SAEF) 프레임워크를 제안한다. SAEF는 magnitude dominance에 의존하는 대신 통계적 합의에 기반해 view를 집계한다. 이론적으로 SAEF는 global scaling에 대한 불변성과 비대칭적 dominance에 대한 강건성을 보장한다. 네 가지 다양한 데이터셋에서의 실험은 SAEF가 정확도와 semantic conflict 및 noise에 대한 robustness 측면에서 state-of-the-art baseline을 능가하며, 심각한 scale perturbation에 대해서도 안정성을 유지함을 확인한다.</p>"},{"id":"61246","en":"FedReLa: Imbalanced Federated Learning via Re-Labeling","ko":"FedReLa: Re-Labeling을 통한 불균형 Federated Learning","authors":"Guangzheng Hu, Patricia Menendez Galvan, Feng Liu, Mingming Gong, Guanghui Wang, Liuhua Peng","pos":"#4207","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=sEPES6oimF","abs":"<p>Federated learning has emerged as the foremost approach for decentralized model training with privacy preserving. The global class imbalance and cross-client data heterogeneity naturally coexist, and the mismatch between local and global imbalances exacerbates the performance degradation of the aggregated model. The agnosticism of global class distribution poses significant challenges for data-level methods, especially under extreme conditions with severe class absence across clients. In this paper, we propose FedReLa, a novel data-level approach that tackles the coexistence of data heterogeneity and class imbalance in federated learning. By re-labeling samples with a feature-dependent label re-allocator, FedReLa corrects biased global decision boundaries without requiring knowledge of the global class distribution. This modular, model-agnostic approach can be integrated with algorithmic methods to deliver consistent improvements without additional communication overhead. Through extensive experiments, our method significantly improves the accuracy of minority classes and the overall accuracy on stepwise-imbalanced and long-tailed datasets, outperforming the previous state of the art.</p>","absKo":"<p>Federated learning은 privacy-preserving한 decentralized model training을 위한 가장 유력한 접근법으로 부상했다. global class imbalance와 cross-client data heterogeneity는 자연스럽게 공존하며, local imbalance와 global imbalance의 불일치는 aggregated model의 성능 저하를 더욱 악화시킨다. global class distribution에 대한 agnosticism은 data-level method에 상당한 도전을 제기하는데, 특히 client 전반에 걸쳐 class가 심하게 결여되는 극단적 상황에서 더욱 그렇다. 본 논문에서는 federated learning에서 data heterogeneity와 class imbalance의 공존을 다루는 새로운 data-level 접근법인 FedReLa를 제안한다. feature-dependent label re-allocator로 sample을 다시 label함으로써, FedReLa는 global class distribution에 대한 지식 없이도 편향된 global decision boundary를 보정한다. 이 modular한 model-agnostic 접근법은 algorithmic method와 통합되어 추가 communication overhead 없이 일관된 성능 향상을 제공할 수 있다. 광범위한 실험을 통해, 우리 방법은 stepwise-imbalanced 및 long-tailed dataset에서 minority class 정확도와 overall accuracy를 크게 향상시키며, 이전 state of the art를 능가함을 보였다.</p>"},{"id":"62550","en":"Learning to Rank by Directly Optimizing Full-Order Probabilities","ko":"전체 확률을 직접 최적화하여 랭킹 학습","authors":"Yongxiang Tang, Chao Wang, Jincheng Lu, Yanhua Cheng, Xialong Liu, Peng Jiang","pos":"#4209","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=fch6yT64ZH","abs":"Learning to rank can be cast as a probabilistic modeling problem over permutations, where the goal is to estimate the likelihood of an observed total ordering of items. This formulation naturally involves full-order probabilities of the form $\\mathbb{P}(\\mathrm{z}_1 &lt; \\cdots &lt; \\mathrm{z}_n)$, whose exact computation and optimization are intractable due to the factorial growth of the permutation space with respect to list size. We introduce the *Full-Order Bound* (FOB), a tractable lower bound on the probability of an observed ordering, constructed from a subset of ordering constraints that factorizes across items while avoiding low-dimensional surrogate objectives and preserving order-reversal invariance. FOB induces a convex inner tightening problem over latent cut points, which we solve efficiently during training using a *safe-region gradient ascent* (SRGA) procedure. Experiments on synthetic ranking tasks and large-scale learning-to-rank benchmarks show that FOB consistently improves performance over pairwise and listwise surrogates, Plackett--Luce style sequential factorization models, and differentiable sorting baselines. Code is available at [https://anonymous.4open.science/r/FOB_2026-46C4](https://anonymous.4open.science/r/FOB_2026-46C4).","absKo":"learning to rank는 순열 위의 확률적 모델링 문제로 볼 수 있으며, 목표는 관측된 아이템의 전체 순서(total ordering)가 나타날 확률을 추정하는 것이다. 이 정식화는 자연스럽게 $\\mathbb{P}(\\mathrm{z}_1 &lt; \\cdots &lt; \\mathrm{z}_n)$ 형태의 full-order probability를 포함하는데, 리스트 크기에 따라 순열 공간이 factorial하게 커지므로 이를 정확히 계산하고 최적화하는 것은 다루기 어렵다. 우리는 관측된 순서의 확률에 대한 계산 가능한 lower bound인 *Full-Order Bound* (FOB)을 제안한다. FOB는 아이템들에 걸쳐 factorize되도록 구성된 ordering constraint의 부분집합에서 만들어지며, 낮은 차원의 surrogate objective를 피하고 order-reversal invariance를 보존한다. FOB는 latent cut point에 대한 convex한 inner tightening 문제를 유도하며, 우리는 이를 training 동안 *safe-region gradient ascent* (SRGA) 절차를 사용해 효율적으로 푼다. 합성 ranking task와 대규모 learning-to-rank benchmark에서의 실험은 FOB가 pairwise 및 listwise surrogate, Plackett--Luce 스타일의 sequential factorization model, 그리고 differentiable sorting baseline보다 일관되게 더 나은 성능을 보임을 보여준다. 코드는 [https://anonymous.4open.science/r/FOB_2026-46C4](https://anonymous.4open.science/r/FOB_2026-46C4)에서 확인할 수 있다."},{"id":"60852","en":"Likelihood over Estimation: Robust Quadratic Discriminant Analysis for Heavy-Tailed Distributions with Theory and Evidence","ko":"추정보다 Likelihood: Heavy-Tailed Distribution을 위한 견고한 Quadratic Discriminant Analysis의 이론과 증거","authors":"Niranjana Ambadi, eugene pinsky","pos":"#4210","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=w1j6MujWuh","abs":"Quadratic Discriminant Analysis (QDA) assumes Gaussian class-conditional distributions, causing systematic misclassification when data exhibit heavy tails. We propose Stable-QDA, which replaces the Gaussian likelihood with a symmetric $\\alpha$-stable likelihood that decays polynomially rather than exponentially in Mahalanobis distance. Crucially, we find that correcting likelihood misspecification yields larger gains than robustifying parameter estimation: standard estimators (sample mean, Ledoit--Wolf covariance) often outperform robust alternatives when class heteroscedasticity is discriminative. We provide consistency guarantees under infinite-variance regimes, data-driven diagnostics for estimator selection, and demonstrate 15--53\\% error reduction on real-world heavy-tailed benchmarks.","absKo":"Quadratic Discriminant Analysis (QDA)는 Gaussian class-conditional distribution을 가정하므로, 데이터가 heavy tail을 보일 때 체계적인 오분류가 발생한다. 우리는 Gaussian likelihood를 Mahalanobis distance에 대해 지수적으로가 아니라 다항식적으로 감소하는 symmetric $\\alpha$-stable likelihood로 대체하는 Stable-QDA를 제안한다. 핵심적으로, likelihood misspecification을 바로잡는 것이 parameter estimation을 robustify하는 것보다 더 큰 성능 향상을 가져온다는 점을 발견했다. 클래스 간 heteroscedasticity가 판별적일 때는 standard estimator(sample mean, Ledoit--Wolf covariance)가 robust alternative보다 더 나은 경우가 많다. 우리는 무한 분산 regime에서의 consistency guarantee, estimator 선택을 위한 data-driven diagnostic을 제시하고, 실제 heavy-tailed benchmark에서 15--53\\%의 오류 감소를 입증한다."},{"id":"63084","en":"On the Power of Statistics in Class-Incremental Learning with Pretrained Models","ko":"사전학습 모델을 활용한 클래스 증분 학습에서 통계의 힘에 관하여","authors":"Zhiwen Cao, Yanfeng Li, Shudong Huang, Yalan Ye, Shuyin Xia, Yi Wang, Jiancheng Lv","pos":"#4211","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=aFV5K8vPAI","abs":"<p>Recent class-incremental learning (CIL) methods built on large pre-trained vision models have shown that strong performance can be retained even under strict data access constraints. This raises a fundamental question: which properties of pre-trained representations make such recovery possible in the class-incremental setting? In this work, we show that class-level feature statistics play a central role in enabling effective CIL under strong pre-training. When the visual backbone is frozen, maintaining simple class-wise statistics—such as prototypes and low-order distributional information—can recover a substantial fraction of the performance achieved by static joint training across diverse benchmarks. We make this observation explicit through deliberately minimal reference points built on frozen CLIP representations. In particular, we demonstrate that competitive performance can be obtained even without continual training, by performing inference directly from accumulated class-level statistics. Our findings suggest that class-level statistics constitute an important and previously underemphasized component of recent CIL approaches based on pre-trained models, offering a complementary perspective for understanding their strong empirical performance.</p>","absKo":"<p>최근 large pre-trained vision model 위에서 구축된 class-incremental learning(CIL) 방법들은 엄격한 data access 제약하에서도 강한 성능을 유지할 수 있음을 보여 주었다. 이는 근본적인 질문을 제기한다. pre-trained representation의 어떤 속성이 class-incremental setting에서 이러한 복원을 가능하게 하는가? 본 연구에서는 class-level feature statistics가 강한 pre-training 하에서 효과적인 CIL을 가능하게 하는 핵심 역할을 한다는 점을 보인다. visual backbone을 freeze한 상태에서 prototype과 low-order distributional information 같은 단순한 class-wise statistics를 유지하는 것만으로도, 다양한 benchmark에서 static joint training이 달성한 성능의 상당 부분을 회복할 수 있다. 우리는 frozen CLIP representation 위에 deliberately minimal reference point를 구성함으로써 이 관찰을 명시적으로 드러낸다. 특히, 누적된 class-level statistics로부터 직접 inference를 수행하는 것만으로도 continual training 없이 경쟁력 있는 성능을 얻을 수 있음을 보여준다. 우리의 결과는 class-level statistics가 pre-trained model 기반 최근 CIL 접근법의 중요한, 그러나 이전에는 덜 강조되었던 구성 요소임을 시사하며, 이들의 강한 실증 성능을 이해하기 위한 보완적 관점을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"66134","en":"Trust Functions: Near Lossless Weak-to-Strong Generalization by Learning to Trust the Weak Teacher","ko":"Trust Functions: 약한 교사를 신뢰하도록 학습하여 거의 손실 없는 Weak-to-Strong 일반화 달성","authors":"Arda Uzunoglu, Alvin Zhang, Daniel Khashabi","pos":"#4214","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=6bXLKr5NMT","abs":"<p>Weak-to-strong generalization studies how to improve a strong student using supervision from a weaker teacher when reliable labels are scarce. We view this primarily as a data selection problem, where the key challenge is to identify which weak labels are reliable enough to serve as a training signal. To address this, we introduce trust functions that assign each weak label a scalar trust score and use these scores to filter weak supervision. Across several domains, including world knowledge, quantitative reasoning, decision making, trust filtering yields students that match and sometimes surpass ground-truth supervision, achieving near-lossless weak-to-strong generalization. Moreover, trust functions enable an iterative weak-to-strong chain that compounds gains by training a student and reusing it as the next teacher, producing the strongest final model. Our analyses suggest that neural trust functions improve learning through more than label error reduction. They induce an implicit easy-first curriculum, recover near-optimal alternatives where ground truth labels are incomplete, and produce more coherent gradient updates, offering a mechanistic account of the stability and efficiency of trust-filtered weak-to-strong generalization.</p>"},{"id":"64703","en":"Trustworthy Federated Label Distribution Learning under Annotation Quality Disparity","ko":"Annotation 품질 격차 하의 신뢰할 수 있는 Federated Label Distribution Learning","authors":"Tianyue Niu, Zhiqiang Kou, Hongwei Zeng, Wenke Huang, Biao Liu, Hanlin Gu, Yuheng Jia, Di Jiang, Yang Liu, Xin Geng","pos":"#4215","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=KhqHSH9xKk","abs":"<p>Label Distribution Learning (LDL) models supervision as an instance-wise probability distribution, enabling fine-grained learning under inherent ambiguity, but its success relies on high-fidelity label distributions that are costly to obtain and thus often noisy.  Motivated by privacy-sensitive applications, we study Federated Label Distribution Learning (Fed-LDL), where data isolation further induces heterogeneous annotation quality across clients, making local updates unevenly reliable and breaking sample-size-based aggregation (e.g., FedAvg).  To address this trust dilemma, we propose FedQual, a quality-aware Fed-LDL framework with two coupled mechanisms: (i) quality-adaptive client training guided by a global semantic anchor that calibrates low-quality clients while preserving high-quality autonomy, and (ii) reliability-aware server aggregation that reweights client contributions by effective reliable information rather than raw sample size.  To enable rigorous evaluation, we construct four new Fed-LDL benchmarks (FER-LDL, FI-LDL, PIPAL-LDL, and KADID-LDL) with controlled annotation quality disparity.  We further provide a theoretical guarantee showing that under heterogeneous supervision quality, client-specific calibration is strictly better than any uniform calibration.  Extensive experiments on the proposed benchmarks demonstrate the effectiveness of FedQual.</p>","absKo":"<p>Label Distribution Learning (LDL)은 supervision을 instance 단위의 probability distribution으로 모델링하여, 본질적인 ambiguity 하에서도 세밀한 학습을 가능하게 하지만, 그 성공은 획득 비용이 크기 때문에 종종 noisy한 고정밀 label distribution에 의존한다. privacy-sensitive application에 동기를 두어, 우리는 Federated Label Distribution Learning (Fed-LDL)을 연구한다. 여기서 data isolation은 client 간 annotation quality의 이질성을 추가로 유발하며, local update의 신뢰도를 불균등하게 만들고 sample-size 기반 aggregation(FedAvg 등)을 무너뜨린다. 이러한 trust dilemma를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 FedQual을 제안한다. 이는 두 개의 결합된 메커니즘을 갖는 quality-aware Fed-LDL framework이다. (i) global semantic anchor에 의해 guided되는 quality-adaptive client training으로, low-quality client를 보정하면서 high-quality autonomy는 보존하고, (ii) raw sample size가 아니라 effective reliable information에 따라 client contribution을 재가중하는 reliability-aware server aggregation이다. 엄밀한 평가를 가능하게 하기 위해, 우리는 annotation quality disparity가 제어된 네 개의 새로운 Fed-LDL benchmark(FER-LDL, FI-LDL, PIPAL-LDL, KADID-LDL)를 구축한다. 또한 heterogeneous supervision quality 하에서, client-specific calibration이 어떤 uniform calibration보다도 엄격하게 더 우수함을 보이는 이론적 보장을 제시한다. 제안한 benchmark에 대한 광범위한 실험은 FedQual의 효과를 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"60998","en":"When More Experts Hurt: Underfitting in Multi-Expert Learning to Defer","ko":"전문가가 많을수록 해로울 때: Multi-Expert Learning to Defer의 Underfitting","authors":"Shuqi Liu, Yuzhou Cao, Lei Feng, Bo An, Luke Ong","pos":"#4216","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=uhNn8S6rEb","abs":"<p>Learning to Defer (L2D) enables a classifier to abstain from predictions and defer to an expert, and has recently been extended to multi-expert settings. In this work, we show that multi-expert L2D is fundamentally more challenging than the single-expert case. With multiple experts, the classifier's underfitting becomes inherent, which seriously degrades prediction performance, whereas in the single-expert setting it arises only under specific conditions. We theoretically reveal that this stems from an intrinsic expert identifiability issue: learning which expert to trust from a diverse pool, a problem absent in the single-expert case and renders existing underfitting remedies failed. To tackle this issue, we propose PiCCE (<strong>Pi</strong>ck the <strong>C</strong>onfident and <strong>C</strong>orrect <strong>E</strong>xpert), a surrogate-based method that adaptively identifies a reliable expert based on empirical evidence. PiCCE effectively reduces multi-expert L2D to a single-expert–like learning problem, thereby resolving multi-expert underfitting.  We further prove its statistical consistency and ability to recover class probabilities and expert accuracies.  Extensive experiments across diverse settings, including real-world expert scenarios, validate our theoretical results and demonstrate improved performance.</p>","absKo":"Learning to Defer(L2D)는 classifier가 예측을 보류하고 expert에게 defer할 수 있게 하며, 최근 multi-expert setting으로 확장되었다. 본 연구에서는 multi-expert L2D가 single-expert case보다 본질적으로 더 어렵다는 점을 보인다. 여러 expert가 존재하면 classifier의 underfitting은 내재적인 현상이 되어 prediction performance를 심각하게 저하시킨다. 반면 single-expert setting에서는 특정 조건에서만 나타난다. 우리는 이 현상이 본질적인 expert identifiability issue에서 비롯됨을 이론적으로 밝힌다. 즉, 다양한 expert pool에서 누구를 신뢰할지 학습하는 문제이며, 이는 single-expert case에는 존재하지 않고 기존 underfitting remedy를 무력화한다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해 우리는 PiCCE(<strong>Pi</strong>ck the <strong>C</strong>onfident and <strong>C</strong>orrect <strong>E</strong>xpert)를 제안한다. 이는 empirical evidence를 바탕으로 신뢰할 수 있는 expert를 적응적으로 식별하는 surrogate-based method이다. PiCCE는 multi-expert L2D를 효과적으로 single-expert와 유사한 learning problem으로 줄여 multi-expert underfitting을 해결한다. 우리는 또한 이 방법의 statistical consistency와 class probability 및 expert accuracy를 복원할 수 있는 능력을 증명한다. 실제 expert scenario를 포함한 다양한 setting에서의 광범위한 실험은 이론적 결과를 검증하고 향상된 성능을 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"64585","en":"PINE: Pruning Boosted Tree Ensembles with Conformal In-Distribution Prediction Equivalence","ko":"PINE: Conformal In-Distribution Prediction Equivalence를 활용한 Boosted Tree Ensemble Pruning","authors":"Haruki Yajima, Yusuke Matsui","pos":"#4301","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=LxAy8UpVUC","abs":"Tree ensembles are machine learning models with strong predictive performance and interpretability, and remain widely used for tabular data. Standard pruning methods for tree ensembles typically optimize an accuracy–compression trade-off and may change a subset of predictions, potentially compromising decision consistency. Faithful pruning methods address this issue by preserving prediction equivalence over the entire input space, but this requirement leads to lower compression ratios. We propose **PINE**, a pruning method that provides strong guarantees within an in-distribution region. PINE preserves prediction equivalence within this region and controls the region size using a single parameter $\\\\alpha$ via conformal calibration. Experiments on 12 public tabular datasets show that PINE improves the compression ratio by up to 30% while maintaining a comparable rate of prediction equivalence to existing faithful pruning methods. As a result, PINE achieves an improved equivalence–compression trade-off.","absKo":"Tree ensembles는 강한 예측 성능과 해석가능성을 갖는 machine learning model이며, tabular data에서 여전히 널리 사용된다. Tree ensemble에 대한 표준 pruning method는 일반적으로 accuracy–compression trade-off를 최적화하며 예측의 일부를 변경할 수 있어 decision consistency를 저해할 가능성이 있다. Faithful pruning method는 전체 input space에 걸쳐 prediction equivalence를 보존함으로써 이 문제를 해결하지만, 이러한 요구사항은 더 낮은 compression ratio로 이어진다. 우리는 in-distribution region 내에서 강한 보장을 제공하는 pruning method인 **PINE**을 제안한다. PINE은 이 region 내에서 prediction equivalence를 보존하고, conformal calibration을 통해 하나의 파라미터 $\\\\alpha$로 region 크기를 제어한다. 12개의 공개 tabular dataset에 대한 실험은 PINE이 기존 faithful pruning method와 비슷한 prediction equivalence rate를 유지하면서 compression ratio를 최대 30%까지 향상시킴을 보여준다. 그 결과 PINE은 개선된 equivalence–compression trade-off를 달성한다."},{"id":"61421","en":"Federated Data and Feature Selection by Generalized CUR Decomposition","ko":"Generalized CUR Decomposition을 통한 Federated Data and Feature Selection","authors":"Yingpeng Tang, Zhuang Qi, Xiaoli Tang, Wei Zhuo, Sheng-Jun Huang, Han Yu","pos":"#4305","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=qLfDHsMojZ","abs":"<p>With the advance of federated learning (FL) in privacy-sensitive domains such as healthcare, finance, and mobile intelligence, the need for efficient and robust training becomes increasingly urgent. Communication bottlenecks, heterogeneous client distributions, and fairness requirements make it essential to select the “right” data and features for model training. Yet existing FL research often addresses feature selection and data selection separately, ignoring their interplay in real-world high-dimensional and noisy datasets, leading to suboptimal performance. In this paper, we propose a unified framework for data and feature selection by formulating the problem as a generalized CUR decomposition problem. We introduce FedGCUR, a practical framework that integrates a federated column-pivoted QR (FedCPQR) decomposition routine with per-silo row selection. Specifically, FedCPQR is designed to securely compute a global pivot order without exposing raw data, while FedGCUR leverages this to jointly select shared features and silo-specific samples. We prove that FedCPQR produces exactly the same decomposition results as centralized CPQR and establish an upper bound of the reconstruction error of FedGCUR. Extensive empirical results show that the proposed framework achieves higher accuracy compared to the baselines of data and feature selection methods, demonstrating its effectiveness and efficiency.</p>","absKo":"<p>의료, 금융, 모바일 지능과 같이 프라이버시가 중요한 영역에서 federated learning(FL)이 발전함에 따라, 효율적이고 강건한 학습의 필요성은 점점 더 절실해지고 있다. 통신 병목, 이질적인 클라이언트 분포, 공정성 요구는 모델 학습을 위해 “올바른” 데이터와 feature를 선택하는 것을 필수적으로 만든다. 그러나 기존 FL 연구는 feature selection과 data selection을 별도로 다루는 경우가 많아, 실제 고차원·노이즈 데이터셋에서 두 요소의 상호작용을 간과함으로써 최적 이하의 성능을 초래한다. 본 논문에서는 문제를 generalized CUR decomposition 문제로 정식화하여 data와 feature selection을 위한 통합 프레임워크를 제안한다. 우리는 federated column-pivoted QR(FedCPQR) decomposition 루틴과 silo별 row selection을 통합한 실용적 프레임워크 FedGCUR를 소개한다. 구체적으로 FedCPQR은 원시 데이터를 노출하지 않으면서 전역 pivot 순서를 안전하게 계산하도록 설계되었고, FedGCUR는 이를 활용해 공유 feature와 silo별 sample을 공동으로 선택한다. 우리는 FedCPQR이 centralized CPQR과 정확히 동일한 decomposition 결과를 생성함을 증명하고, FedGCUR의 reconstruction error에 대한 상한을 제시한다. 광범위한 실험 결과는 제안한 프레임워크가 data 및 feature selection 방법들의 baseline에 비해 더 높은 정확도를 달성함을 보여주며, 그 효과성과 효율성을 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"64628","en":"MePo: Meta Post-Refinement for Rehearsal-Free General Continual Learning","ko":"MePo: Rehearsal-Free 일반 Continual Learning을 위한 Meta Post-Refinement","authors":"Guanglong Sun, Hongwei Yan, Liyuan Wang, Zhiqi KANG, Shuang Cui, Hang Su, Jun Zhu, Yi Zhong","pos":"#3117","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=LXZcSgqldO","abs":"<p>To cope with uncertain changes of the external world, intelligent systems must continually learn from complex, evolving environments and respond in real time. This ability, collectively known as general continual learning (GCL), encapsulates practical challenges such as online datastreams and blurry task boundaries. Although leveraging pretrained models (PTMs) has greatly advanced conventional continual learning (CL), these methods remain limited in reconciling the diverse and temporally mixed information along a single pass, resulting in sub-optimal GCL performance. Inspired by meta-plasticity and reconstructive memory in neuroscience, we introduce here an innovative approach named <strong>Me</strong>ta <strong>Po</strong>st-Refinement (MePo) for PTMs-based GCL. This approach constructs pseudo task sequences from pretraining data and develops a bi-level meta-learning paradigm to refine the pretrained backbone, which serves as a prolonged pretraining phase but greatly facilitates rapid adaptation of representation learning to downstream GCL tasks. MePo further initializes a meta covariance matrix as the reference geometry of pretrained representation space, enabling GCL to exploit second-order statistics for robust output alignment. MePo serves as a plug-in strategy that achieves significant performance gains across a variety of GCL benchmarks and pretrained checkpoints in a rehearsal-free manner (e.g., 15.10%, 13.36%, and 12.56% on CIFAR-100, ImageNet-R, and CUB-200 under Sup-21/1K).</p>","absKo":"<p>외부 세계의 불확실한 변화에 대응하기 위해, 지능형 시스템은 복잡하고 진화하는 환경으로부터 지속적으로 학습하고 실시간으로 반응할 수 있어야 한다. 일반 continual learning (GCL)로 통칭되는 이러한 능력은 online datastream과 흐릿한 task boundary와 같은 실용적 과제를 포괄한다. pretrained models (PTMs)를 활용하는 것이 기존 continual learning (CL)을 크게 발전시켰지만, 이러한 방법들은 단일 pass에서 다양하고 시간적으로 혼합된 정보를 조화시키는 데 여전히 한계가 있어, 최적보다 낮은 GCL 성능으로 이어진다. 신경과학의 meta-plasticity와 reconstructive memory에서 영감을 받아, 우리는 PTMs-based GCL을 위한 <strong>Me</strong>ta <strong>Po</strong>st-Refinement (MePo)라는 혁신적 접근을 제안한다. 이 접근은 pretraining data로부터 pseudo task sequence를 구성하고, pre-trained backbone을 refine하기 위한 bi-level meta-learning paradigm을 개발한다. 이는 긴 pretraining phase처럼 작동하지만 downstream GCL task에 대한 representation learning의 빠른 적응을 크게 촉진한다. MePo는 또한 meta covariance matrix를 pretrained representation space의 reference geometry로 초기화하여, GCL이 robust output alignment를 위해 second-order statistic을 활용할 수 있게 한다. MePo는 rehearsal-free 방식으로 다양한 GCL benchmark와 pretrained checkpoint 전반에서 유의미한 성능 향상을 달성하는 plug-in strategy로 기능한다(예: Sup-21/1K 설정에서 CIFAR-100, ImageNet-R, CUB-200에서 각각 15.10%, 13.36%, 12.56%).</p>"},{"id":"61653","en":"OPIC: Enhancing Language Model Merging via Optimizing In-Context Capability","ko":"OPIC: In-Context Capability 최적화를 통한 Language Model 병합 개선","authors":"Jie He, Chao Chen, Weidong Bao, Zhengyi Zhong, Shuai Zhang, Ji Wang","pos":"#1906","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=o4OEtKVpGE","abs":"<p>Task-vector–based model merging enables low-cost, training-free multi-task learning for large language models, but suffers from severe performance degradation due to task conflict. Prior mitigation strategies largely rely on validation data for costly hyperparameter tuning, limiting both interpretability and practicality. We therefore propose OPIC, an evolutionary optimization–based model merging framework. Our preliminary experiments reveal that the degradation of In-Context Learning (ICL) capabilities is a primary driver of task conflict. Motivated by this insight, we formulate model merging as an optimization problem with ICL preservation as the objective. OPIC  introduces a hierarchical refinement operators and optimizes it using self-generated data, effectively eliminating the reliance on external validation sets. Experimental results demonstrate that OPIC achieves an average performance retention of 80.73%, outperforming SOTA methods and improving by up to 11.1% over recent validation-free approaches. In addition, OPIC is compatible with existing merging pipelines, offering a new alternative solution for deploying without validation dependencies. Code is available at: https://anonymous.4open.science/r/OPIC-CFFE.</p>","absKo":"<p>task-vector 기반 model merging은 large language model을 위한 저비용의 training-free multi-task learning을 가능하게 하지만, task conflict로 인해 심각한 성능 저하를 겪습니다. 기존 완화 전략은 대체로 비용이 큰 hyperparameter tuning을 위해 validation data에 의존하므로, 해석 가능성과 실용성 모두를 제한합니다. 이에 우리는 OPIC, 즉 evolutionary optimization 기반 model merging framework를 제안합니다. 우리의 예비 실험은 In-Context Learning(ICL) 능력의 저하가 task conflict의 주요 원인임을 보여줍니다. 이 통찰에 동기를 얻어, 우리는 model merging을 ICL 보존을 목표로 하는 최적화 문제로 정식화합니다. OPIC는 hierarchical refinement operator를 도입하고 self-generated data를 사용해 이를 최적화함으로써 외부 validation set에 대한 의존을 효과적으로 제거합니다. 실험 결과, OPIC는 평균 80.73%의 performance retention을 달성하여 SOTA 방법들을 능가하고, 최근의 validation-free 접근법보다 최대 11.1% 향상됨을 보였습니다. 또한 OPIC는 기존 merging pipeline과 호환되어, validation dependency 없이 배포하기 위한 새로운 대안적 해법을 제공합니다. 코드는 다음에서 उपलब्ध합니다: https://anonymous.4open.science/r/OPIC-CFFE.</p>"},{"id":"64956","en":"Saliency-Aware Model Merging","ko":"Saliency 인식 Model Merging","authors":"Jungin Park, Jiyoung Lee, Kwanghoon Sohn","pos":"#2709","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=IMKni29CXX","abs":"<p>Model merging aims to consolidate multiple task-specific models fine-tuned on different datasets into a unified architecture that performs cross-domain proficiency.     Current data-free model merging methods often struggle to scale as they rely on simple parameter-level heuristics that ignore inter-layer dependencies and non-uniform distribution of expertise.     To address this, we propose SA-Merging, a new basis for model merging that estimates the saliency of each parameter through a differentiable inter-layer interaction function.     By leveraging the gradients of this function with merged parameters, we derive a saliency score that identifies parameters critical to preserving end-to-end information flows.     Building on this signal, SA-Merging recursively eliminates non-informative parameters in a purely data-free manner.     Notably, our method is inherently modular, seamlessly integrating with existing sign-based and sparsification-based interference mitigation strategies.     Furthermore, we extend SA-Merging to introduce rank-wise saliency decomposition for LoRA, enabling the integration of low-rank adapters without compromising their structural integrity.     Extensive experiments on vision and language tasks demonstrate the effectiveness of our saliency-based approach, further reducing the gap between data-free and test-time adaptation methods.</p>"},{"id":"68807","en":"Localize-and-Stitch: Efficient Model Merging via Sparse Task Arithmetic","ko":"Localize-and-Stitch: Sparse Task Arithmetic을 통한 효율적 모델 병합","authors":"Yifei He, Yuzheng Hu, Yong LIN, Tong Zhang, Han Zhao","pos":"#2815","abs":"Model merging offers an effective strategy to combine the strengths of multiple finetuned models into a unified model that preserves the specialized capabilities of each. Existing methods merge models in a global manner, performing arithmetic operations across all model parameters. However, such global merging often leads to task interference, degrading the performance of the merged model. In this work, we introduce Localize-and-Stitch, a novel approach that merges models in a localized way. Our algorithm works in two steps: i) Localization: identify tiny ($1\\%$ of the total parameters) localized regions in the finetuned models containing essential skills for the downstream tasks, and ii) Stitching: reintegrate only these essential regions back into the pretrained model for task synergy. We demonstrate that our approach effectively locates sparse regions responsible for finetuned performance, and the localized regions could be treated as compact and interpretable representations of the finetuned models (tasks). Empirically, we evaluate our method on various vision and language benchmarks, showing that it outperforms existing model merging methods under different data availability scenarios. Beyond strong empirical performance, our algorithm also facilitates model compression and preserves pretrained knowledge, enabling flexible and continual skill composition from multiple finetuned models with minimal storage and computational overhead."},{"id":"63291","en":"Unlocking the Potential of Continual Model Merging: An ODE Perspective","ko":"지속적 모델 병합의 잠재력 잠금 해제: ODE 관점","authors":"Lihong Lin, Haidong Kang","pos":"#3003","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=YLL4QeBbDD","abs":"<p>Continual Model Merging (CMM) enables rapid customization of foundation models across sequentially arriving tasks, offering a scalable alternative to repeated retraining. However, existing merging rules lack explicit controllability over the allocation of learning capacity between previously learned capabilities and newly merged models. Consequently, as tasks are merged sequentially, this deficiency accumulates into severe forgetting, particularly in scenarios with heterogeneous task importance, where performance allocation becomes highly inconsistent. The key reason can be attributed to the fact that previous methods treat each task model as an isolated parameter point and apply fixed algebraic combinations, rather than explicitly constructing a transition that respects how independently trained models can be connected in parameter space. Motivated by mode connectivity, we assume that desirable merged models lie on low loss connecting paths, and that continual merging should follow such paths without crossing loss barriers that induce forgetting. Grounded in these insights, we propose a novel ODE-driven Merging (ODE-M) tailored for CMM that traces such a path by integrating a time-dependent velocity field and enforcing barrier constraints to prevent loss-increasing steps. Extensive experiments demonstrate that ODE-M achieves state-of-the-art performance compared to its competitors across mainstream CMM benchmarks.</p>","absKo":"<p>Continual Model Merging (CMM)은 순차적으로 도착하는 task에 걸쳐 foundation model을 신속하게 맞춤화할 수 있게 하며, 반복적인 재학습에 대한 확장 가능한 대안을 제공한다. 그러나 기존 merging rule은 이전에 학습한 능력과 새롭게 병합되는 model 사이에 학습 용량을 어떻게 배분할지에 대한 명시적 제어가 부족하다. 그 결과 task를 순차적으로 병합할수록 이러한 결함이 누적되어 심각한 forgetting으로 이어지며, 특히 task 중요도가 이질적인 상황에서는 성능 배분이 매우 일관되지 않게 된다. 핵심 이유는 이전 방법들이 각 task model을 고립된 parameter point로 취급하고 고정된 algebraic combination을 적용할 뿐, 독립적으로 학습된 model이 parameter space에서 어떻게 연결될 수 있는지를 반영하는 transition을 명시적으로 구성하지 않기 때문이다. mode connectivity에 착안하여, 우리는 바람직한 merged model이 낮은 loss를 잇는 path 위에 놓여 있으며 continual merging은 forgetting을 유발하는 loss barrier를 넘지 않는 이런 path를 따라가야 한다고 가정한다. 이러한 통찰에 기반하여, 우리는 time-dependent velocity field를 적분하고 loss 증가 step을 막기 위해 barrier constraint를 부과함으로써 그러한 path를 추적하는 CMM 전용의 새로운 ODE-driven Merging (ODE-M)을 제안한다. 광범위한 실험은 ODE-M이 주요 CMM benchmark 전반에서 경쟁 방법들보다 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"65918","en":"The Geometry of Updates: Fisher Alignment at Vocabulary Scale","ko":"업데이트의 기하학: 어휘 규모에서의 Fisher 정렬","authors":"John Sweeney","pos":"#4002","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=8vkE9kvrXa","abs":"Predicting transferability within shared-output model families (e.g., LLMs that share a vocabulary) poses a dilemma: representation-similarity metrics can be uninformative without assumptions about error geometry, while update-geometry metrics are computationally prohibitive. We show that, in a shared-output head setting, representation metrics (e.g., CKA) are non-identifiable for transfer; models can share identical representations yet have orthogonal head updates, so CKA alone cannot reliably rank transfer. We make head Fisher alignment tractable at vocabulary scale ($K{=}128{,}256$) using FisherSketch, a streaming algorithm that compresses joint (activation, error) geometry to a 16KB task signature ($m{=}4096$) with a 192KB per-task streaming state. Beyond the head, we prove a full-network decomposition and bounds, and we propose measurable diagnostics (profile cosine and off-diagonal discrepancy). We validate these on ViT-B/16 and LLMs up to 70B, showing that head/block approximations track the full Fisher and that FisherSketch remains informative in fixed-prefix verbalizer-shift settings where activation similarity cannot distinguish tasks."},{"id":"63513","en":"When Shared Knowledge Hurts: Spectral Over-Accumulation in Model Merging","ko":"공유 지식이 해가 될 때: 모델 병합에서의 스펙트럼 과잉 축적","authors":"Yayuan Li, Ze Peng, Jian Zhang, Jintao Guo, Yue Duan, Yinghuan Shi","pos":"#4101","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=WUjk3RVZyV","abs":"Model merging combines multiple fine-tuned models into a single model by $\\textit{adding}$ their weight updates, providing a lightweight alternative to retraining. Existing methods primarily target resolving conflicts between task updates, leaving the failure mode of over-counting shared knowledge unaddressed. We show that when tasks share aligned spectral directions (\\ie, overlapping singular vectors), a simple linear combination repeatedly accumulates these directions, inflating the singular values and biasing the merged model toward shared subspaces. To mitigate this issue, we propose Singular Value Calibration (SVC), a training-free and data-free post-processing method that quantifies subspace overlap and rescales inflated singular values to restore a balanced spectrum. Across vision and language benchmarks, SVC consistently improves strong merging baselines and achieves state-of-the-art performance. Furthermore, by modifying only the singular values, SVC improves the performance of Task Arithmetic by 13.0\\%.","absKo":"모델 병합(model merging)은 여러 fine-tuned model의 weight update를 $\\textit{더함}$으로써 이를 하나의 모델로 결합하며, 재학습에 대한 가벼운 대안이 된다. 기존 방법은 주로 task update 간 충돌을 해결하는 데 초점을 맞추는 반면, 공유 지식을 과도하게 집계하는 실패 양상은 다루지 않는다. 우리는 task가 정렬된 spectral direction(즉, 겹치는 singular vector)을 공유할 때, 단순한 선형 결합이 이 방향들을 반복적으로 누적하여 singular value를 증폭시키고 merged model을 shared subspace 쪽으로 편향시킨다는 점을 보인다. 이 문제를 완화하기 위해, 우리는 subspace overlap을 정량화하고 증폭된 singular value를 재조정하여 균형 잡힌 spectrum을 복원하는 training-free, data-free post-processing 방법인 Singular Value Calibration(SVC)을 제안한다. vision 및 language benchmark 전반에서 SVC는 강력한 merging baseline을 일관되게 개선하며 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성한다. 더 나아가 singular value만 수정함으로써, SVC는 Task Arithmetic의 성능을 13.0\\% 향상시킨다."},{"id":"62524","en":"Transporting Task Vectors across Different Architectures without Training","ko":"아키텍처가 다른 태스크 벡터를 학습 없이 전이","authors":"Filippo Rinaldi, Aniello Panariello, Giacomo Salici, Angelo Porrello, Simone Calderara","pos":"#4102","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=foyE0eF8HW","abs":"<p>Adapting large pre-trained models to downstream tasks often produces task-specific parameter updates that are expensive to relearn for every model variant. While recent work has shown that such updates can be transferred between models with identical architectures, transferring them across models of different widths remains largely unexplored. In this work, we introduce Theseus, a training-free method for transporting task-specific updates across heterogeneous models. Rather than matching parameters directly, we characterize a task update by the functional effect it induces on intermediate representations. We formalize task-vector transport as a functional matching problem on observed activations and show that, after aligning representation spaces via orthogonal Procrustes analysis, it admits a stable closed-form solution that preserves the geometry of the update. We evaluate Theseus on vision and language models across different widths, showing consistent improvements over strong baselines without additional training or backpropagation. Our results show that task updates can be meaningfully transferred across architectures when task identity is defined functionally rather than parametrically.</p>","absKo":"<p>대규모 pre-trained model을 downstream task에 맞게 적응시키면, 각 model variant마다 다시 학습하기에는 비용이 큰 task-specific parameter update가 생성되는 경우가 많다. 최근 연구는 이러한 update를 동일한 architecture를 가진 model 사이에서는 전이할 수 있음을 보였지만, 서로 다른 width를 가진 model 사이의 전이는 아직 충분히 탐구되지 않았다. 본 연구에서는 이질적인 model 간에 task-specific update를 옮기는 training-free 방법인 Theseus를 소개한다. 우리는 parameter를 직접 맞추는 대신, 중간 representation에 유도되는 functional effect를 통해 task update를 특징화한다. 관측된 activation 위에서 task-vector transport를 functional matching problem으로 정식화하고, orthogonal Procrustes analysis를 통해 representation space를 정렬한 뒤에는 update의 geometry를 보존하는 안정적인 closed-form solution이 존재함을 보인다. 우리는 서로 다른 width를 가진 vision 및 language model에 대해 Theseus를 평가하여, 추가 학습이나 backpropagation 없이도 강력한 baseline보다 일관된 개선을 달성함을 보인다. 우리의 결과는 task identity를 parametric이 아니라 functional하게 정의할 때, task update가 architecture 간에 의미 있게 전이될 수 있음을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"65449","en":"Symbiosis-Inspired Knowledge Distillation for Incremental Object Detection","ko":"증분 객체 탐지를 위한 공생에서 영감을 받은 지식 증류","authors":"Mingyue Zeng, De Cheng, Zhipeng Xu, Huaijie Wang, Nannan Wang, Xinbo Gao","pos":"#4103","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=DYCt9JtCra","abs":"<p>Incremental object detection (IOD) aims to extend detectors to new categories while retaining previously acquired knowledge. Existing methods often adopt a class incremental learning perspective, separating feature spaces to sharpen decision boundaries. However, this paradigm conflicts with the inherent object symbiosis in detection, where objects naturally co-occur or occlude one another, creating spatial and semantic dependencies that necessitate a shared feature space. Ignoring these dependencies distorts the shared representations, exacerbates confusion between old and new classes, and accelerates catastrophic forgetting. To address this, we propose Symbiosis-Inspired Knowledge Distillation (SIKD), which explicitly leverages object symbiosis at two complementary levels. Spatial Symbiosis Distillation (SpSD) focuses on symbiotic regions where the old model responds with high overlap to objects in the new task. It preserves generalizable old class cues, suppresses class-specific bias and redundancy, and distills the refined evidence to the new model at matched spatial locations with slot-aligned supervision. Semantic Symbiosis Distillation (SeSD) maintains class level structure by forming confidence weighted prototypes for old classes and aligning their inter class soft ranks over the old class logits, which stabilizes the semantic topology during adaptation. Extensive experiments demonstrate the effectiveness and superiority of the proposed method. Code is available in the supplementary material.</p>"},{"id":"63880","en":"SyMerge: From Non-Interference to Synergistic Merging via Single-Layer Adaptation","ko":"SyMerge: 단일 층 적응을 통한 비간섭에서 시너지적 병합으로","authors":"Aecheon Jung, Seunghwan Lee, Dongyoon Han, Sungeun Hong","pos":"#4104","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=SroXgWAQll","abs":"<p>Model merging combines independently trained models into a single multi-task model. However, most existing approaches focus primarily on avoiding task interference. We argue that its greater potential lies in enabling task synergy, where tasks actively improve one another. We identify cross-task performance, defined by compatibility between encoders and predictors across tasks, as a key indicator of merge quality. We demonstrate that adapting only a single task-specific layer is sufficient to induce such synergy. This study proposes SyMerge, a lightweight framework that jointly optimizes merging coefficients and a single task-specific layer. We adopt an expert-guided self-labeling objective, providing stable supervision beyond entropy minimization. Intriguingly, we further show that SyMerge successfully merges models trained from different initializations, a regime where standard methods break down. Our minimalist yet principled method achieves state-of-the-art results across vision, dense prediction, and NLP benchmarks.</p>","absKo":"<p>Model merging은 독립적으로 학습된 모델들을 하나의 multi-task model로 결합하는 방법이다. 그러나 기존 접근법의 대부분은 주로 task interference를 피하는 데 초점을 맞춘다. 우리는 그보다 더 큰 잠재력은 task synergy, 즉 task들이 서로를 능동적으로 향상시키는 데 있다고 주장한다. 우리는 merge quality의 핵심 지표로, task들 간 encoder와 predictor의 호환성으로 정의되는 cross-task performance를 식별한다. 또한 task-specific layer 하나만 적응시키는 것만으로도 이러한 synergy를 유도하기에 충분함을 보인다. 본 연구는 merging coefficient와 single task-specific layer를 jointly optimize하는 lightweight framework인 SyMerge를 제안한다. 우리는 entropy minimization을 넘어 안정적인 supervision을 제공하는 expert-guided self-labeling objective를 채택한다. 흥미롭게도, 우리는 SyMerge가 서로 다른 initialization에서 학습된 모델들까지 성공적으로 merge할 수 있음을 추가로 보인다. 이는 standard method들이 무너지는 regime이다. 우리의 minimalist하면서도 principled한 방법은 vision, dense prediction, NLP benchmark 전반에서 state-of-the-art 결과를 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"60572","en":"Sketch-Based Low-Rank Model Merging with Shared Circulant Transforms","ko":"공유 순환 변환을 이용한 스케치 기반 저랭크 모델 병합","authors":"Zhiming Zhang, Rong Yin, Xiaoshuai Hao, Hansong Zhang, Hao Peng, Yong Liu, Can Ma, Dan Meng","pos":"#4105","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ytlRCCl7Pf","abs":"<p>Merging multiple low-rank adapters (LoRA) provides a practical route to scaling multi-task learning and deployment more efficiently than full-model weight merging, while avoiding reliance on task-specific training data. However, most existing approaches either treat LoRA updates as dense weight deltas or depend on expensive subspace factorizations, making the merge step a primary latency bottleneck. To address this issue, this paper establishes a theoretically positive relationship between merging quality and the effective rank of the matrices being merged. Motivated by this insight, we propose <strong>CircuMerge</strong>, a sketch-based framework for low-rank model merging built on shared circulant transforms. Especially, this approach treats each adapter as a pair of low-rank matrices and applies a shared circulant transform to align all tasks in a common coordinate system. This alignment enables more efficient sampling, allowing us to generate compact sketches that effectively summarize the interactions between tasks. These compact sketches enable applying the merging rules directly to them and reconstructing a standard low-rank adapter, preserving the essential information while significantly reducing computational overhead. Across a broad multi-task LoRA benchmarks covering both vision and language settings, extensive empirical results demonstrate that CircuMerge reduces the overall merging time by at least 44\\% compared to the state-of-the-art approaches, with accuracy matching or exceeding the optimal level.</p>","absKo":"<p>여러 low-rank adapter(LoRA)를 병합하는 것은 task-specific training data에 의존하지 않으면서도, full-model weight merging보다 더 효율적으로 multi-task learning과 배포를 확장할 수 있는 실용적인 경로를 제공한다. 그러나 기존 방법의 대부분은 LoRA update를 dense weight delta로 취급하거나, 비용이 큰 subspace factorization에 의존하여 merge 단계가 주요 latency 병목이 된다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해, 본 논문은 병합 품질과 병합되는 matrix의 effective rank 사이에 이론적으로 양의 상관관계가 있음을 보인다. 이러한 통찰에 동기를 얻어, 우리는 공유 circulant transform 위에 구축된 low-rank model merging을 위한 sketch-based framework인 <strong>CircuMerge</strong>를 제안한다. 특히 이 방법은 각 adapter를 low-rank matrix의 쌍으로 간주하고, 공유 circulant transform을 적용하여 모든 task를 공통 coordinate system에 정렬한다. 이러한 정렬은 더 효율적인 sampling을 가능하게 하며, 이를 통해 task 간 상호작용을 효과적으로 요약하는 compact sketch를 생성할 수 있다. 이 compact sketch는 merging rule을 직접 적용할 수 있게 하고 standard low-rank adapter를 재구성할 수 있게 하여, 본질적인 정보를 보존하면서도 computational overhead를 크게 줄인다. vision과 language 설정을 모두 포괄하는 광범위한 multi-task LoRA benchmark 전반에서 수행한 대규모 실험 결과, CircuMerge는 state-of-the-art 방법과 비교해 전체 merging time을 최소 44\\% 줄이면서도 정확도는 최적 수준과 같거나 이를 상회함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"64416","en":"Revisiting the Role of Pretrained Weights in Model Merging: On Near-Optimality within the Core Subspace","ko":"모델 병합에서 사전학습 가중치의 역할 재고: 핵심 부분공간 내 근최적성에 관하여","authors":"Wenju Sun, Qingyong Li, Tiancheng Li, Yangliao Geng, Albert Boyang Li","pos":"#4106","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=NrGCh79ANM","abs":"<p>Model merging offers an efficient solution for integrating task-specific knowledge from multiple fine-tuned models. Most existing approaches focus on manipulating the difference vectors between fine-tuned and pre-trained weights, often overlooking the generalization capabilities inherent in the pretrained parameters themselves. In this work, we revisit the role of pretrained weights in model merging and investigate their efficacy from a subspace perspective. We find that the components of pretrained weights residing in the core subspace—defined by the dominant singular vectors—are essential for maintaining generalization across diverse tasks. Specifically, we present empirical evidence that pretrained weights are nearly first-order stationary and exhibit predominantly non-negative curvature within this core subspace with respect to multi-task loss landscapes, indicating near-optimality. These findings suggest that task-specific adaptations should be injected primarily into the orthogonal complement of the core subspace, thereby preserving the generalization properties of the pretrained model. Extensive experiments on vision and vision-language tasks show that this subspace-aware strategy consistently yields improvements over state-of-the-art training-free merging methods, including Task Arithmetic, LOT Merging, ISO, and TSV.</p>","absKo":"<p>Model merging은 여러 fine-tuned model로부터 task-specific knowledge를 통합하는 효율적인 방법을 제공한다. 기존 방법의 대부분은 fine-tuned weight와 pretrained weight의 차이 벡터를 조작하는 데 집중하며, 종종 pretrained parameter 자체에 내재된 generalization 능력을 간과한다. 본 연구에서는 model merging에서 pretrained weight의 역할을 재검토하고, subspace 관점에서 그 효용을 조사한다. 우리는 dominant singular vector로 정의되는 core subspace에 존재하는 pretrained weight의 성분이 다양한 task 전반에서 generalization을 유지하는 데 필수적임을 발견했다. 구체적으로, 우리는 pretrained weight가 core subspace 내에서 거의 first-order stationary하며, multi-task loss landscape에 대해 주로 non-negative curvature를 보인다는 실증적 증거를 제시하며, 이는 거의 최적 상태에 있음을 시사한다. 이러한 결과는 task-specific adaptation을 주로 core subspace의 orthogonal complement에 주입해야 하며, 이를 통해 pretrained model의 generalization 속성을 보존해야 함을 시사한다. vision 및 vision-language task에 대한 광범위한 실험은 이 subspace-aware 전략이 Task Arithmetic, LOT Merging, ISO, TSV를 포함한 최신 training-free merging 방법들보다 일관되게 더 나은 성능을 보임을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"61531","en":"Orthogonal Model Merging","ko":"직교 Model Merging","authors":"Sihan Yang, Kexuan Shi, Weiyang Liu","pos":"#4108","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=pCaeMsqpCa","abs":"<p>Merging finetuned Large Language Models (LLMs) has become increasingly important for integrating diverse capabilities into a single unified model. However, prevailing model merging methods rely on linear arithmetic in Euclidean space, which often destroys the intrinsic geometric properties of pretrained weights, such as hyperspherical energy. To address this, we propose Orthogonal Model Merging (OrthoMerge), a method that performs merging operations on the Riemannian manifold formed by the orthogonal group to preserve the geometric structure of the model’s weights. By mapping task-specific orthogonal matrices learned by Orthogonal Finetuning (OFT) to the Lie algebra, OrthoMerge enables a principled yet efficient integration that takes into account both the direction and intensity of adaptations. In addition to directly leveraging orthogonal matrices obtained by OFT, we further extend this approach to general models finetuned with non-OFT methods (\\eg, low-rank finetuning, full finetuning) via an Orthogonal-Residual Decoupling strategy. This technique extracts the orthogonal components of expert models by solving the orthogonal Procrustes problem, which are then merged on the manifold of the orthogonal group, while the remaining linear residuals are processed through standard additive merging. Extensive empirical results demonstrate the effectiveness of OrthoMerge in mitigating catastrophic forgetting and maintaining model performance across diverse tasks.</p>","absKo":"<p>finetuned Large Language Models (LLMs)을 병합하는 것은 다양한 capability를 하나의 통합 모델로 결합하는 데 점점 더 중요해지고 있다. 그러나 널리 쓰이는 model merging 방법은 Euclidean space에서의 선형 산술에 의존하며, 이는 종종 pretrained weight의 intrinsic geometric property, 예를 들어 hyperspherical energy를 파괴한다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 모델의 weight 기하 구조를 보존하기 위해 orthogonal group으로 형성된 Riemannian manifold 위에서 병합 연산을 수행하는 Orthogonal Model Merging (OrthoMerge)을 제안한다. Orthogonal Finetuning (OFT)으로 학습된 task-specific orthogonal matrix를 Lie algebra로 사상함으로써, OrthoMerge는 adaptation의 방향과 강도를 모두 고려하는 원리적이면서도 효율적인 통합을 가능하게 한다. OFT로부터 직접 얻은 orthogonal matrix를 활용하는 것에 더해, 우리는 이 접근을 non-OFT method(\\eg, low-rank finetuning, full finetuning)로 finetune된 일반 모델로 확장하는 Orthogonal-Residual Decoupling 전략도 제안한다. 이 기법은 orthogonal Procrustes problem을 풀어 expert model의 orthogonal component를 추출하고, 이를 orthogonal group의 manifold에서 병합하는 한편, 나머지 linear residual은 표준 additive merging으로 처리한다. 광범위한 실험 결과는 재앙적 망각을 완화하고 다양한 task 전반에서 모델 성능을 유지하는 OrthoMerge의 효과를 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"63501","en":"Multi-Task Bayesian In-Context Learning","ko":"다중 태스크 베이지안 In-Context 학습","authors":"Qingyang Zhu, Eric Oermann, Kyunghyun Cho","pos":"#4109","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Wcl5b7O2KT","abs":"<p>Bayesian predictive inference provides a principled framework for uncertainty quantification, data efficiency, and robust generalization. However, exact inference is often intractable, and scalable approximations may remain computationally expensive or require restrictive modeling assumptions that degrade predictive performance. Prior-Data Fitted and in-context learning networks have recently emerged as an amortized alternative by learning to map datasets directly to predictive distributions, but existing approaches are tightly coupled to the support of the training prior and lack explicit mechanisms for adapting to new priors at test time, resulting in limited robustness under distribution shift. We introduce a multi-task in-context learning framework for amortized hierarchical Bayesian predictive inference that explicitly represents prior information as a prefix of in-context datasets. A transformer trained on sequences of prior and target tasks learns to adapt its predictions across families of priors. On a suite of evaluations with increasing difficulty, including out-of-meta-distribution heavy-tailed priors and priors with high-dimensional latent structures, our method matches oracle Bayesian predictors while being orders of magnitude faster.</p>","absKo":"<p>Bayesian predictive inference는 uncertainty quantification, data efficiency, robust generalization을 위한 원리적 framework를 제공합니다. 그러나 exact inference는 종종 계산적으로 다루기 어렵고, 확장 가능한 근사 방법도 계산 비용이 크거나 predictive performance를 저하시키는 제한적인 modeling assumptions를 요구할 수 있습니다. Prior-Data Fitted 및 in-context learning network는 최근 dataset을 predictive distribution으로 직접 매핑하도록 학습하는 amortized 대안으로 등장했지만, 기존 접근은 training prior의 support에 강하게 결합되어 있으며 test time에 새로운 priors에 적응하기 위한 명시적 메커니즘이 부족해, distribution shift 하에서 robustness가 제한됩니다. 우리는 prior 정보를 in-context datasets의 prefix로 명시적으로 표현하는 amortized hierarchical Bayesian predictive inference를 위한 multi-task in-context learning framework를 제안합니다. prior와 target task의 sequence로 학습된 transformer는 다양한 priors 전반에 걸쳐 예측을 적응하는 법을 학습합니다. out-of-meta-distribution heavy-tailed priors와 고차원 latent structure를 가진 priors를 포함한, 점점 더 어려워지는 평가 집합에서, 우리의 방법은 oracle Bayesian predictor와 일치하는 성능을 보이면서도 수십 배 더 빠릅니다.</p>"},{"id":"63056","en":"Merge to Remember: Sharpness-Aware Isotropic Merging for Continual Learning","ko":"기억을 위한 병합: 지속 학습을 위한 Sharpness-Aware 등방성 병합","authors":"Qun Yang, Enneng Yang, Li Shen, Wei Chen, Long Lan","pos":"#4110","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=aWfk16EvfM","abs":"<p>Continual learning with large pre-trained models offers significant potential for cross-task knowledge accumulation, but faces critical challenges such as catastrophic forgetting and parameter interference, especially when historical data is unavailable. Existing approaches typically rely on sequential fine-tuning or model merging strategies, yet often overlook the impact of loss landscape sharpness and dominant singular value directions, which leads to subspace misalignment and severe knowledge forgetting. In this paper, we propose the Sharpness-Aware Isotropic Merging (SAIM) framework, which introduces targeted optimizations in both the fine-tuning and merging stages to address these issues. Specifically, SAIM consists of two synergistic modules: (1) a Sharpness-Aware Block Coordinate Descent (SA-BCD) optimizer that guides the model toward flatter minima and selectively updates the most task-sensitive parameters, thereby mitigating parameter interference and enhancing robustness; (2) an adaptive isotropic merging algorithm that dynamically balances the singular value spectrum across tasks, effectively preventing the model from overemphasizing any single task direction, maintaining balanced knowledge representation, and improving subspace alignment. Extensive experiments on vision and language benchmarks demonstrate that SAIM achieves 5-10% higher accuracy than existing methods and maintains robust performance as the number of tasks increases. Ablation studies further validate the effectiveness of the SA-BCD fine-tuning strategy in promoting flat minima and reducing parameter interference, as well as its compatibility with various merging approaches.</p>","absKo":"<p>large pre-trained model을 활용한 continual learning은 task 간 지식 축적에 큰 잠재력을 제공하지만, historical data를 사용할 수 없을 때 특히 catastrophic forgetting과 parameter interference와 같은 중대한 문제에 직면한다. 기존 접근법은 대개 sequential fine-tuning이나 model merging strategy에 의존하지만, loss landscape sharpness와 dominant singular value direction의 영향을 종종 간과하여 subspace misalignment와 심각한 지식 망각을 초래한다. 본 논문에서는 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해 fine-tuning과 merging 단계 모두에 targeted optimization을 도입하는 Sharpness-Aware Isotropic Merging(SAIM) framework를 제안한다. 구체적으로 SAIM은 두 개의 상호 보완적인 모듈로 구성된다. (1) 모델이 더 평평한 minima로 수렴하도록 유도하고 task에 가장 민감한 parameter를 선택적으로 업데이트함으로써 parameter interference를 완화하고 robustness를 향상시키는 Sharpness-Aware Block Coordinate Descent(SA-BCD) optimizer, (2) task 간 singular value spectrum을 동적으로 균형 있게 조정하여 모델이 어떤 단일 task direction에 과도하게 치우치지 않도록 방지하고, 균형 잡힌 지식 표현을 유지하며 subspace alignment를 개선하는 adaptive isotropic merging algorithm. vision과 language benchmark에 대한 광범위한 실험은 SAIM이 기존 방법보다 5-10% 더 높은 accuracy를 달성하고 task 수가 증가해도 강건한 성능을 유지함을 보여준다. Ablation study는 또한 SA-BCD fine-tuning strategy가 flat minima를 촉진하고 parameter interference를 줄이는 데 효과적이며, 다양한 merging approach와도 호환됨을 추가로 검증한다.</p>"},{"id":"62247","en":"Fine-Tune Once, Reuse Across Models: Bayesian Task-Update Factors and Approximations","ko":"한 번 Fine-Tune하고 모델 간 재사용: Bayesian Task-Update Factors 및 근사","authors":"Siyang Guo, Junbo Wang, Zibin Zheng","pos":"#4111","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=iLS4oNpEQ1","abs":"<p>As pre-trained models evolve rapidly, transferring fine-tuning knowledge to updated models without retraining has become a critical challenge. Most existing methods reuse parameter updates, yet the same dataset can induce substantially different updates across base models due to mismatched local loss landscapes, making such transfer unstable. We instead adopt a Bayesian-updating perspective: a base model defines a prior, while fine-tuning contributes a task-update factor that is prior-agnostic, thereby making it feasible to reuse the update across base models. Specifically, we formalize a reusable task-update factor by requiring <em>invariance across base models</em> and <em>a fixed-dimensional parameterization</em>. Our main theoretical result shows that such reusable factors exist when the variational family is a half-space, and it is already maximal among convex families. In particular, an ideal regime arises when the priors and their Bayesian posteriors remain within a shared exponential family, as it always admits a reusable update factor. Building on this existence, we propose ***B<strong>ayesian Task Update <strong>Transfer</strong></strong>(<em>BTransfer</em>), which extracts a reusable task-update factor from a single fine-tuning run and applies it to a new prior. For deep networks, we implement <em>BTransfer</em> with a ``lift–transfer–return'' pipeline: 1) lift model parameters to distributions; 2) transfer the extracted task-update factor in the exponential family distributions; and 3) return the updated posterior distribution to parameter space. Extensive experiments demonstrate that our approach effectively reuses fine-tuning knowledge across models without post-training.</p>","absKo":"<p>사전 학습된 모델이 빠르게 진화함에 따라, 재학습 없이 fine-tuning 지식을 업데이트된 모델로 전달하는 것이 중요한 과제가 되었다. 기존 방법의 대부분은 parameter update를 재사용하지만, 동일한 데이터셋도 base model마다 local loss landscape의 불일치로 인해 상당히 다른 update를 유발할 수 있어 이러한 전이가 불안정하다. 우리는 대신 Bayesian-updating 관점을 취한다: base model은 prior를 정의하고, fine-tuning은 prior에 무관한 task-update factor를 기여하므로, 이를 통해 다른 base model들 사이에서 update를 재사용할 수 있다. 구체적으로, 우리는 <em>base model 간 불변성</em>과 <em>고정 차원 parameterization</em>을 요구함으로써 재사용 가능한 task-update factor를 정식화한다. 우리의 주요 이론 결과는 변분 family가 half-space일 때 이러한 재사용 가능한 factor가 존재하며, 그것이 이미 convex family들 중에서 최대임을 보여준다. 특히, prior와 그 Bayesian posterior가 공유 exponential family 안에 머무르는 이상적인 regime가 나타나며, 이 경우 항상 재사용 가능한 update factor를 허용한다. 이러한 존재성에 기반하여, 우리는 ***B<strong>ayesian Task Update <strong>Transfer</strong></strong>(<em>BTransfer</em>)를 제안한다. 이는 단일 fine-tuning 실행에서 재사용 가능한 task-update factor를 추출하여 새로운 prior에 적용한다. deep network의 경우, 우리는 <em>BTransfer</em>를 ``lift–transfer–return'' pipeline으로 구현한다: 1) model parameter를 distribution으로 lift하고; 2) 추출된 task-update factor를 exponential family distribution에서 transfer하며; 3) 업데이트된 posterior distribution을 parameter space로 return한다. 광범위한 실험은 우리의 접근법이 post-training 없이도 모델 간 fine-tuning 지식을 효과적으로 재사용함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"63681","en":"ECA: Efficient Continual Alignment for Open-Ended Image-to-Text Generation.","ko":"ECA: 열린 끝 이미지-텍스트 생성을 위한 효율적 지속 정렬","authors":"Jiangtao Kong, Peijun Zhao, Chun-Fu (Richard) Chen, Youngwook Do, Shaohan Hu, Tianyi Zhou, Huajie Shao","pos":"#4112","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=UfiLIUtbSO","abs":"<p>Incremental Learning (IL) for Open-ended Image-to-Text Generation (OpenITG) enables models to continuously generate accurate, contextually relevant text for new images while preserving previously acquired knowledge. Unlike prior studies, this paper addresses a more practical scenario in which the predominant category of visual data shifts over time as environments evolve. In this context, we introduce a new notion of continual alignment, which incrementally adapts the alignment module within pre-trained VLMs to preserve high-quality cross-modal representations. Based on this idea, we propose <strong>E</strong>fficient <strong>C</strong>ontinual <strong>A</strong>lignment (ECA), a novel exemplar-free IL approach for OpenITG. The key challenge is enabling the model to acquire new, task-specific features while minimizing interference with the established alignment without accessing raw data from previous tasks. To address this, ECA employs three core mechanisms: a <strong>M</strong>ixture <strong>o</strong>f <strong>Q</strong>uery (MoQ) module that adapts task-specific query tokens, a <strong>F</strong>ish<strong>e</strong>r <strong>D</strong>ynamic <strong>Ex</strong>pansion (FeDEx) that dynamically expands model structure based on a Fisher Information Matrix (FIM)-based metric, and an embedding dictionary with <strong>D</strong>ictionary <strong>R</strong>eplay (DR) to retain past knowledge. To evaluate ECA's performance, we construct four new IL OpenITG benchmarks that better reflect real-world scenarios. Experimental results demonstrate that ECA significantly mitigates catastrophic forgetting and improves IL performance compared to baseline methods. Benchmarks are available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/ECA-ToS-Benchmarks-FB17.</p>","absKo":"<p>Open-ended Image-to-Text Generation (OpenITG)을 위한 Incremental Learning (IL)은 모델이 이전에 습득한 지식을 보존하면서 새로운 이미지에 대해 정확하고 문맥적으로 적절한 텍스트를 지속적으로 생성할 수 있게 한다. 기존 연구와 달리, 본 논문은 환경이 진화함에 따라 시각 데이터의 주된 범주가 시간에 따라 변화하는 보다 실용적인 시나리오를 다룬다. 이러한 맥락에서 우리는 pre-trained VLMs 내의 alignment module을 점진적으로 적응시켜 고품질 cross-modal representation을 보존하는 continual alignment라는 새로운 개념을 제안한다. 이 아이디어에 기반하여, 우리는 OpenITG를 위한 새로운 exemplar-free IL 방법인 <strong>E</strong>fficient <strong>C</strong>ontinual <strong>A</strong>lignment (ECA)를 제안한다. 핵심 과제는 이전 task의 raw data에 접근하지 않고도, 기존 alignment와의 간섭을 최소화하면서 새로운 task-specific feature를 획득하도록 모델을 만드는 것이다. 이를 위해 ECA는 세 가지 핵심 메커니즘을 사용한다: task-specific query token을 적응시키는 <strong>M</strong>ixture <strong>o</strong>f <strong>Q</strong>uery (MoQ) module, Fisher Information Matrix (FIM)-기반 metric에 따라 모델 구조를 동적으로 확장하는 <strong>F</strong>ish<strong>e</strong>r <strong>D</strong>ynamic <strong>Ex</strong>pansion (FeDEx), 그리고 과거 지식을 유지하기 위한 <strong>D</strong>ictionary <strong>R</strong>eplay (DR)를 포함한 embedding dictionary이다. ECA의 성능을 평가하기 위해, 우리는 실제 세계 시나리오를 더 잘 반영하는 네 개의 새로운 IL OpenITG benchmark를 구축한다. 실험 결과, ECA는 catastrophic forgetting을 유의미하게 완화하고 baseline method들에 비해 IL 성능을 향상시킴을 보여준다. Benchmark는 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/ECA-ToS-Benchmarks-FB17 에서 제공된다.</p>"},{"id":"66438","en":"Distilling Task-Level Coordination Policies for Generalizable Multi-Agent Cooperation","ko":"일반화 가능한 다중 에이전트 협력을 위한 작업 수준 조정 정책 증류","authors":"Zimo Zhai, Manjie Xu, Wei Liang","pos":"#4113","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=3jqSwyWi9t","abs":"<p>Large language models have shown strong reasoning abilities and are increasingly explored as high-level coordinators for multi-agent systems. However, directly deploying LLMs for coordination remains challenging, as effective policies often fail to reliably emerge at the low-level control level, and inference costs limit scalability.  We propose SynCoord (Synthetic Coordination Distillation), a self-supervised pipeline that distills task-level decision-making for cooperation from high-capacity reasoning models into lightweight agent policies. Our approach does not rely on explicit supervision or handcrafted coordination rules. Instead, we define a set of task-level tool interfaces that constrain LLM interaction and enable the collection of interaction trajectories, which are then used to train compact coordinated policies. This distillation process transfers coordination behaviors that are difficult to elicit through prompting alone, while substantially reducing inference overhead at execution time.  We evaluate our method in the multi-agent cooperation benchmark Overcooked-AI with varying team sizes and environment layouts. Experimental results show that the distilled policies achieve success rates and efficiency comparable to reinforcement learning–based methods, while exhibiting fewer erroneous or redundant actions and generalizing across team sizes without retraining.</p>"},{"id":"63494","en":"Component-Wise Composite Likelihood Distillation for Censored Time-to-Event Data","ko":"검열된 사건 발생 시간 데이터를 위한 구성 요소별 복합 우도 증류","authors":"Feiyang Deng, Lingfeng Luo, Jiayu Zhou, Kevin He","pos":"#4114","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=WgrRyHYbo5","abs":"<p>Accurate survival modeling in biomedical studies is often hindered by rare events, limited effective sample sizes, and settings with limited or partially observed information (e.g., covariates of interest that are difficult or expensive to collect, highly-structured sampling designs, or nuisance parameters omitted by conditioning). Knowledge distillation can leverage external predictive information without sharing individual-level data, but existing approaches are largely built for fully specified likelihoods or probability-based survival models and do not extend to settings where outcome distributions are only partially specified. To address this challenge, we propose a knowledge distillation framework based on a composite-likelihood Kullback–Leibler divergence that aligns teacher and student models within components. Our key insight is that, although composite likelihoods do not define a global outcome distribution, each likelihood component induces a well-defined probability model on its restricted outcome space, enabling a principled KL divergence. Simulation studies and biomedical case studies show improved discrimination and estimation efficiency in rare-event, heterogeneous settings without requiring access to external individual-level data.</p>","absKo":"<p>생의학 연구에서 정확한 survival modeling은 희귀 사건, 제한된 effective sample size, 그리고 제한적이거나 부분적으로 관측된 information이 있는 setting(예: 수집이 어렵거나 비용이 큰 관심 covariate, highly-structured sampling design, 또는 conditioning으로 인해 생략된 nuisance parameter) 때문에 종종 저해된다. Knowledge distillation은 개별 수준 데이터를 공유하지 않고도 외부 predictive information을 활용할 수 있지만, 기존 접근은 대체로 fully specified likelihood 또는 probability-based survival model을 위해 만들어져 있으며 outcome distribution이 부분적으로만 명세되는 setting으로는 확장되지 않는다. 이 과제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 component 내에서 teacher와 student model을 정렬하는 composite-likelihood Kullback–Leibler divergence 기반 knowledge distillation framework를 제안한다. 우리의 핵심 통찰은 composite likelihood가 전역 outcome distribution을 정의하지는 못하지만, 각 likelihood component가 제한된 outcome space 위에서 well-defined probability model을 유도하므로, 원칙적인 KL divergence를 구성할 수 있다는 점이다. 시뮬레이션 연구와 생의학 case study는 외부 개별 수준 데이터에 접근할 필요 없이 희귀 사건의 heterogeneous setting에서 discrimination과 estimation efficiency를 향상시킴을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"63900","en":"CE$^4$L: Continual Ego, Exo, and Ego-Exo Learning","ko":"CE$^4$L: 지속적 ego, exo, ego-exo 학습","authors":"Hongwei Yan, Kanglei Zhou, Yuchen Liu, Qingyu Shi, Yi Zhong, Liyuan Wang","pos":"#4115","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Shb4ltB3J2","abs":"Perception for embodied agents is video-based, often multi-view (ego, exo, or both), and inherently continual, with simultaneous task and viewpoint shifts. Yet continual learning (CL) remains dominated by exo-only recognition tasks, obscuring behavior under these real-world coupled shifts. We introduce **C**ontinual **E**go, **E**xo, and **E**go-**E**xo **L**earning (**CE$^4$L**), a unified multi-view CL benchmark spanning four representative tasks: cross-view referenced skill assessment, temporal action segmentation, cross-view association, and action anticipation \\&amp; planning. CE$^4$L highlights challenges largely absent in prior CL benchmarks, including cross-view correspondence, view-dependent asynchrony, and heterogeneous semantic objectives. To this end, we propose **V**ideo **I**ncremental **S**ubspace-routed **T**ask **A**dapters (**VISTA**), a parameter-efficient baseline method that stores task-specific updates in lightweight adapters and performs training-free routing via residual distance to task-specific whitened subspaces estimated from second-order statistics. Extensive experiments demonstrate the significantly varied efficacy of representative CL methods across CE$^4$L settings, while VISTA is consistently competitive and achieves state-of-the-art overall performance.","absKo":"embodied agent를 위한 perception은 video-based이며, 종종 multi-view(ego, exo, 또는 둘 다)이고, task와 viewpoint의 동시 변화를 수반하므로 본질적으로 continual하다. 그럼에도 continual learning (CL)은 exo-only recognition task에 의해 주도되어 왔고, 이러한 실제 세계의 결합된 변화 하에서의 동작을 가리고 있다. 우리는 **C**ontinual **E**go, **E**xo, and **E**go-**E**xo **L**earning(**CE$^4$L**)을 제안한다. 이는 cross-view referenced skill assessment, temporal action segmentation, cross-view association, action anticipation \\&amp; planning의 네 가지 대표 task를 포괄하는 통합 multi-view CL benchmark이다. CE$^4$L은 이전 CL benchmark에서는 거의 드러나지 않았던 cross-view correspondence, view-dependent asynchrony, heterogeneous semantic objective를 포함한 여러 난제를 부각한다. 이를 위해 우리는 **V**ideo **I**ncremental **S**ubspace-routed **T**ask **A**dapters (**VISTA**)를 제안한다. VISTA는 task-specific update를 경량 adapter에 저장하는 parameter-efficient baseline method이며, second-order statistics로 추정한 task-specific whitened subspace까지의 residual distance를 이용해 training-free routing을 수행한다. 대규모 실험은 CE$^4$L 설정 전반에서 대표적인 CL method들의 효용이 크게 달라짐을 보여주며, VISTA는 일관되게 경쟁력 있는 성능을 보이고 전체적으로 state-of-the-art를 달성한다."},{"id":"63062","en":"AlignedNorm: Prompting Vision–Language Models via Coupled Prompt Field","ko":"AlignedNorm: 결합 프롬프트 필드를 통한 Vision-Language 모델 프롬프팅","authors":"Qi Ma, Chen-Yang Wang, Dehong Gao, Deng-Ping Fan","pos":"#4116","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=aQAWAtrxxe","abs":"<p>Prompt learning for vision-language models (VLMs) primarily follows end-to-end or decoupled routes to balance base and new task performance, but suffers a fundamental bottleneck: sample-wise optimization within task-specific feature spaces traps models in local optima, hindering global optimality. To address this, we identify a key insight that VLMs can be prompted within a Coupled Prompt Field-a shared space where base and new tasks are mutually constrained-and present AlignedNorm, which enforces the field coupling. By dynamically aligning the norms of prompts to VLMs' native scale, our method enables joint optimization of both tasks.  Without complex designs, our method matches leading decoupled approaches on 15 datasets across 4 experimental settings, offering both a new perspective and a practical solution to the local-optima dilemma in prompt learning.</p>","absKo":"<p>vision-language models (VLMs)의 prompt learning은 주로 base task와 new task 성능의 균형을 맞추기 위해 end-to-end 또는 decoupled 경로를 따르지만, 근본적인 병목을 안고 있다. task-specific feature space 내부에서의 sample-wise optimization은 모델을 local optimum에 가두어 global optimality를 저해한다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 VLMs가 Coupled Prompt Field, 즉 base task와 new task가 상호 제약을 받는 shared space 안에서 prompt될 수 있다는 핵심 통찰을 제시하고, field coupling을 강제하는 AlignedNorm을 소개한다. prompt의 norm을 VLM의 고유 scale에 동적으로 맞춤으로써, 우리의 방법은 두 task의 joint optimization을 가능하게 한다. 복잡한 설계 없이도, 우리의 방법은 4개의 실험 설정에서 15개 데이터셋에 걸쳐 선도적인 decoupled 접근법과 맞먹는 성능을 보이며, prompt learning에서의 local-optima 딜레마에 대한 새로운 관점과 실용적 해법을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"60721","en":"Strategy-Aware Optimization Modeling with Reasoning LLMs","ko":"추론 LLM을 활용한 Strategy-Aware 최적화 모델링","authors":"Ruiqing Zhao, Fengzhi Li, Yuan Zuo, Rui Liu, YanSong Liu, Yunfei Ma, Fanyu Meng, JUNLAN FENG","pos":"#3801","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=xEN1n4vu1j","abs":"<p>Large language models (LLMs) can generate syntactically valid optimization programs, yet often struggle to reliably choose an effective modeling strategy, leading to incorrect formulations and inefficient solver behavior. We propose <strong>SAGE</strong>, a strategy-aware framework that makes <em>Modeling Strategy</em> explicit in both data construction and post-training. SAGE builds a solver-verified multi-strategy dataset and trains a student model with supervised fine-tuning followed by Segment-Weighted GRPO using a composite reward over format compliance, correctness, and solver efficiency. Across eight benchmarks spanning synthetic and real-world settings, SAGE improves average pass@1 from 72.7 to 80.3 over the strongest open-source baseline. With multiple generations, SAGE discovers more distinct correct formulations and improves component-level diversity at pass@16 by 19-29%. At the largest scale, SAGE produces more compact constraint systems with 14.2% fewer constraints than the baseline, consistent with solver-efficient modeling. Overall, these results show that making <em>Modeling Strategy</em> explicit improves automated optimization modeling. Code is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/SAGE-F25B/.</p>","absKo":"<p>대규모 언어 모델(LLMs)은 문법적으로 올바른 optimization program을 생성할 수 있지만, 효과적인 modeling strategy를 안정적으로 선택하는 데는 여전히 어려움을 겪으며, 그 결과 잘못된 formulation과 비효율적인 solver 동작으로 이어지곤 한다. 우리는 <strong>SAGE</strong>를 제안하는데, 이는 데이터 구성과 post-training 모두에서 <em>Modeling Strategy</em>를 명시적으로 다루는 strategy-aware framework이다. SAGE는 solver로 검증된 multi-strategy dataset을 구축하고, supervised fine-tuning에 이어 format compliance, correctness, solver efficiency에 대한 composite reward를 사용하는 Segment-Weighted GRPO로 student model을 학습한다. synthetic 및 real-world setting을 아우르는 8개 benchmark에서 SAGE는 가장 강력한 open-source baseline 대비 average pass@1을 72.7에서 80.3으로 향상시킨다. 여러 번의 generation을 사용할 때 SAGE는 더 다양한 distinct correct formulation을 발견하고, pass@16에서 component-level diversity를 19-29% 향상시킨다. 가장 큰 규모에서는 SAGE가 baseline보다 constraints 수를 14.2% 줄인 더 compact한 constraint system을 생성하며, 이는 solver-efficient modeling과 일치한다. 전반적으로 이러한 결과는 <em>Modeling Strategy</em>를 명시적으로 만드는 것이 automated optimization modeling을 향상시킨다는 점을 보여준다. 코드는 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/SAGE-F25B/ 에서 확인할 수 있다.</p>"},{"id":"64673","en":"Near-Optimal Convergence of Accelerated Gradient Methods under Generalized and $(L_0,L_1)$-Smoothness","ko":"일반화된 $(L_0,L_1)$-Smoothness 하의 Accelerated Gradient Method의 준최적 수렴","authors":"Alexander Tyurin","pos":"#3903","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=L0T4pmqkMg","abs":"We study first‐order methods for convex optimization problems with functions $f$ satisfying the recently proposed $\\ell$-smoothness condition $||\\nabla^{2}f(x)|| \\le \\ell\\left(||\\nabla f(x)||\\right),$ which generalizes the $L$-smoothness and $(L_{0},L_{1})$-smoothness. While accelerated gradient descent (AGD) is known to reach the optimal complexity $\\mathcal{O}(\\sqrt{L} R / \\sqrt{\\varepsilon})$ under $L$-smoothness, where $\\varepsilon$ is an error tolerance and $R$ is the distance between a starting and an optimal point, existing extensions to $\\ell$-smoothness either incur extra dependence on the initial gradient, suffer exponential factors in $L_{1} R$, or require costly auxiliary sub-routines, leaving open whether an AGD‐type $\\mathcal{O}(\\sqrt{\\ell(0)} R / \\sqrt{\\varepsilon})$ rate is possible for small-$\\varepsilon$, even in the $(L_{0},L_{1})$-smoothness case. We resolve this open question. Developing new proof techniques, we achieve $\\mathcal{O}(\\sqrt{\\ell(0)} R / \\sqrt{\\varepsilon})$ oracle complexity for small-$\\varepsilon$ and virtually any $\\ell$. For instance, for $(L_{0},L_{1})$-smoothness, our bound $\\mathcal{O}(\\sqrt{L_0} R / \\sqrt{\\varepsilon})$ is provably optimal in the small-$\\varepsilon$ regime and removes all non-constant multiplicative factors present in prior accelerated algorithms.","absKo":"우리는 최근 제안된 $\\ell$-smoothness 조건 $||\\nabla^{2}f(x)|| \\le \\ell\\left(||\\nabla f(x)||\\right)$을 만족하는 함수 $f$를 갖는 convex optimization 문제에 대한 first-order method를 연구한다. 이 조건은 $L$-smoothness와 $(L_{0},L_{1})$-smoothness를 일반화한다. Accelerated gradient descent(AGD)는 $L$-smoothness 하에서 최적 복잡도 $\\mathcal{O}(\\sqrt{L} R / \\sqrt{\\varepsilon})$에 도달하는 것으로 알려져 있는데, 여기서 $\\varepsilon$는 error tolerance이고 $R$은 시작점과 최적점 사이의 거리이다. 그러나 $\\ell$-smoothness로의 기존 확장은 초기 gradient에 대한 추가 의존성을 수반하거나, $L_{1} R$에 대한 exponential factor를 겪거나, 값비싼 auxiliary sub-routine을 필요로 하여, $(L_{0},L_{1})$-smoothness 경우조차 작은 $\\varepsilon$에서 AGD형 $\\mathcal{O}(\\sqrt{\\ell(0)} R / \\sqrt{\\varepsilon})$ rate가 가능한지 여부는 미해결로 남아 있었다. 우리는 이 열린 문제를 해결한다. 새로운 proof technique을 개발하여, 작은 $\\varepsilon$와 사실상 임의의 $\\ell$에 대해 $\\mathcal{O}(\\sqrt{\\ell(0)} R / \\sqrt{\\varepsilon})$ oracle complexity를 달성한다. 예를 들어 $(L_{0},L_{1})$-smoothness의 경우, 우리의 bound $\\mathcal{O}(\\sqrt{L_0} R / \\sqrt{\\varepsilon})$는 작은 $\\varepsilon$ regime에서 이론적으로 최적임이 증명되며, 이전 accelerated algorithm에 존재하던 모든 비상수 multiplicative factor를 제거한다."},{"id":"61933","en":"Distributionally Robust Set Representation Learning Under Inference-Time Element Corruption","ko":"추론 시점 element corruption 하에서 분포적으로 강건한 집합 표현 학습","authors":"Yankai Chen, Hanrong Zhang, Bowei He, Philip Yu, Xue Liu","pos":"#1505","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=lZqQN9Ji21","abs":"<p>Standard Set Representation Learning methods typically excel on curated data but often overlook the challenge of Inference-time Element Corruption. This refers to scenarios where deployed models encounter element-level degradations, such as outliers or missing components, that may distort the set representation and degrade performance. To address this, we propose SW-DRSO, a distributionally robust optimization framework tailored for sets. Rather than minimizing loss solely on the observed training data, SW-DRSO optimizes the worst-case expected loss over a family of plausible inference-time variations. We further introduce a barycentric adversary that transforms the intractable search for worst-case corrupted sets into a differentiable and efficient optimization process. Extensive experiments across four tasks demonstrate that SW-DRSO effectively enhances robustness against corruption while maintaining high overall performance.</p>","absKo":"<p>표준 Set Representation Learning 방법은 일반적으로 정제된 데이터에서는 뛰어난 성능을 보이지만, Inference-time Element Corruption이라는 문제는 자주 간과한다. 이는 배포된 모델이 outlier나 결측 구성요소와 같은 element 수준의 손상을 마주해 set representation이 왜곡되고 성능이 저하되는 상황을 의미한다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 set에 특화된 distributionally robust optimization 프레임워크인 SW-DRSO를 제안한다. 관측된 학습 데이터에서의 loss만 최소화하는 대신, SW-DRSO는 가능한 inference-time variation의 집합에 대해 최악의 경우 기대 loss를 최적화한다. 또한 우리는 barycentric adversary를 도입하여, 최악의 손상된 set을 찾는 비해석적 탐색을 미분 가능하고 효율적인 최적화 과정으로 변환한다. 네 가지 task에 걸친 광범위한 실험은 SW-DRSO가 전반적인 높은 성능을 유지하면서도 corruption에 대한 robustness를 효과적으로 향상시킴을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"66426","en":"Draft-and-Audit Reinforcement Learning for Optimization Modeling","ko":"최적화 모델링을 위한 Draft-and-Audit 강화 학습","authors":"Zeping Min, Weihang Xu, Zhengzhong You, Wotao Yin, Xinshang Wang","pos":"#2105","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=3rzJANFrMp","abs":"<p>Natural language to optimization (NL2Opt) requires translating unstructured text into executable mathematical models. Beyond simple syntax errors, this task suffers from silent modeling failures, where incorrect formulations execute successfully but yield invalid results. We propose Draft-and-Audit RL (DA-RL), a framework that learns optimization modeling as a two-step iterative workflow. Unlike inference-time scaffolds that rely on intermediate solver feedback to guide repairs, DA-RL optimizes a shared-parameter policy using terminal-only verification: the model is rewarded solely based on the execution of the final audited program. This constraint forces the model to internalize rubric-guided revision as a learned capability and encourages the emergence of cross-turn synergy, where the policy learns to generate drafts that are structurally amenable to self-correction.</p>"},{"id":"65703","en":"Threshold-Guided Optimization for Visual Generative Models","ko":"시각 생성 모델을 위한 임계값 유도 최적화","authors":"Jinbin Bai, Yu Lei, Qingyu Shi, Aosong Feng, Yi Xin, Zhuoran Zhao, Fei Shen, Kaidong Yu, Xiangtai Li","pos":"#2400","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=B258ihKAk9","abs":"<p>Aligning large visual generative models with human feedback is often performed through pairwise preference optimization. While such approaches are conceptually simple, they fundamentally rely on annotated pairs, limiting scalability in settings where feedback is collected as independent scalar ratings. In this work, we revisit the KL-regularized alignment objective and show that the optimal policy implicitly compares each sample’s reward to an instance-specific baseline that is generally intractable. We propose a threshold-guided alignment framework that replaces this oracle baseline with a data-driven global threshold estimated from empirical score statistics. This formulation turns alignment into a binary decision task on unpaired data, enabling effective optimization directly from scalar feedback. We further incorporate a confidence weighting term to emphasize samples whose scores deviate strongly from the threshold, improving sample efficiency. Experiments across both diffusion and masked generative paradigms, spanning three test sets and five reward models, show that our method consistently improves preference alignment over previous methods. These results position our threshold-guided framework as a simple yet principled alternative for aligning visual generative models without paired comparisons.</p>"},{"id":"62214","en":"Inconsistency-Aware Minimization: Improving Generalization with Unlabeled Data","ko":"Inconsistency-Aware Minimization: 라벨 없는 데이터로 일반화 성능 향상","authors":"Hee-Sung Kim, Hyeonseong Kim, Sungyoon Lee","pos":"#2900","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=icRbM5ArwW","abs":"Estimating the generalization gap and developing optimization methods that improve generalization are crucial for deep learning models, for both theoretical understanding and practical applications. Leveraging unlabeled data for these purposes offers significant advantages in real-world scenarios. This paper introduces a novel generalization measure, $\\textit{local inconsistency}$, derived from an information-geometric perspective on the parameter space of neural networks. A key feature of local inconsistency is that it can be computed without explicit labels. We establish theoretical underpinnings by connecting local inconsistency to the Fisher information matrix and the loss Hessian. Empirically, we demonstrate that local inconsistency correlates with the generalization gap. Based on these findings, we propose Inconsistency-Aware Minimization (IAM), which incorporates local inconsistency into the training objective. We demonstrate that in standard supervised learning settings, IAM enhances generalization, achieving performance comparable to that of existing methods such as Sharpness-Aware Minimization. Furthermore, IAM exhibits efficacy in semi- and self-supervised learning scenarios, where the local inconsistency is computed from unlabeled data.","absKo":"일반화 간극을 추정하고 일반화를 향상시키는 최적화 방법을 개발하는 것은 이론적 이해와 실용적 응용 모두에서 deep learning model에 매우 중요하다. 이러한 목적을 위해 unlabeled data를 활용하면 실제 환경에서 상당한 장점을 얻을 수 있다. 본 논문은 neural network의 parameter space에 대한 information-geometric 관점에서 도출된 새로운 generalization measure인 $\\textit{local inconsistency}$를 소개한다. local inconsistency의 핵심 특징은 명시적인 label 없이 계산할 수 있다는 점이다. 우리는 이를 Fisher information matrix와 loss Hessian에 연결함으로써 이론적 기반을 확립한다. 경험적으로는 local inconsistency가 generalization gap과 상관됨을 보인다. 이러한 결과를 바탕으로, 우리는 local inconsistency를 training objective에 포함하는 Inconsistency-Aware Minimization(IAM)을 제안한다. 표준 supervised learning 설정에서 IAM이 Sharpness-Aware Minimization과 같은 기존 방법에 필적하는 성능으로 일반화를 향상시킴을 보인다. 또한 IAM은 semi-supervised 및 self-supervised learning 시나리오에서도 효과를 보이며, 이 경우 local inconsistency는 unlabeled data로부터 계산된다."},{"id":"63046","en":"SOLAR for Offline MARL: Plateau-Triggered Potential Shaping under World-Model Uncertainty","ko":"오프라인 MARL을 위한 SOLAR: 월드 모델 불확실성 하의 정체 유발 잠재력 셰이핑","authors":"Jusheng Zhang, Yijia Fan, Ruiqi Chen, Jing Yang, Ziliang Chen, Yongsen Zheng, Yanxi Chen, Jian Wang, Kwok Yan Lam, Liang Lin, Keze Wang","pos":"#3605","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=aa0XMDcCQb","abs":"Reward shaping can accelerate reinforcement learning, but in sparse-reward \\emph{offline} multi-agent RL it is often brittle: dense intrinsic rewards may alter the underlying Markov game, while world-model guidance can amplify model bias. We find that shaping becomes reliable when it is (i) activated only after \\emph{statistically validated} learning plateaus and (ii) constrained to \\emph{potential-based} shaping, which preserves the task optimum. Motivated by this, we propose \\textsc{SOLAR}, a simulate--evaluate--shape framework. A learned world model enables low-cost rollouts to test plateaus; once a plateau is detected, we inject shaping in the form $r+\\gamma\\Phi(s')-\\Phi(s)$ with adaptively updated potentials; and we attenuate shaping using uncertainty-aware throttling in unreliable regions. We provide theoretical analysis on policy invariance and on the deviation of plateau decisions under model error, and establish stability for the resulting two-timescale adaptation. Experiments on sparse-reward offline MARL benchmarks show consistent gains in stability and final performance across dataset qualities.","absKo":"Sparse-reward \\emph{offline} multi-agent RL에서 reward shaping은 reinforcement learning을 가속할 수 있지만, 종종 취약하다. dense intrinsic reward는 underlying Markov game을 바꿀 수 있고, world-model guidance는 model bias를 증폭시킬 수 있기 때문이다. 우리는 shaping이 (i) \\emph{statistically validated}된 learning plateau 이후에만 활성화되고, (ii) task optimum을 보존하는 \\emph{potential-based} shaping으로 제한될 때 신뢰할 수 있음을 발견했다. 이를 바탕으로 우리는 simulate--evaluate--shape framework인 \\textsc{SOLAR}를 제안한다. 학습된 world model은 저비용 rollout을 가능하게 하여 plateau를 테스트하고, plateau가 감지되면 적응적으로 갱신되는 potential을 사용해 $r+\\gamma\\Phi(s')-\\Phi(s)$ 형태의 shaping을 주입한다. 또한 불확실한 영역에서는 uncertainty-aware throttling으로 shaping을 완화한다. 우리는 policy invariance와 model error 하에서 plateau decision의 deviation에 대한 이론적 분석을 제공하고, 그 결과로 생기는 two-timescale adaptation의 stability를 확립한다. sparse-reward offline MARL benchmark에서의 실험은 다양한 dataset quality에 걸쳐 안정성과 최종 성능 모두에서 일관된 향상을 보여준다."},{"id":"61338","en":"Non-Parametric Optimization for Scalable Learning in Stochastic Decision Problems","ko":"확률적 의사결정 문제의 확장 가능한 학습을 위한 비모수 최적화","authors":"Mohsen Amidzade, Lauri Viitasaari, Mario Di Francesco","pos":"#3700","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=rD79qEJ5iR","abs":"<p>Stochastic optimization (SO) plays a central role in addressing decision‐making problems under uncertainty. Among them, time-varying stochastic optimization (TV-SO) is particularly important due to its applications in adaptive control and machine learning. Non-parametric approaches have been proposed for time-varying deterministic optimization, however, they have not been devised for their stochastic counterparts. This work specifically addresses non-parametric optimality by developing a stochastic variational framework based on Malliavin calculus. This framework enables deriving non-parametric optimality conditions for SO problems with a stochastic decision and supports the design of a scalable deep-learning algorithm that is insensitive to the parameterization dimension. Such an algorithm, called the stochastic path follower (SPF), is applied to solve two key problems under distribution drift, namely least-squares recovery and logistic regression. Experimental results show the merit of the proposed approach against learning-based and gradient-based methods in the state of the art in terms of both performance and scalability.</p>","absKo":"<p>Stochastic optimization (SO)은 불확실성 하의 의사결정 문제를 다루는 데 핵심적인 역할을 한다. 그중에서도 time-varying stochastic optimization (TV-SO)은 adaptive control과 machine learning에서의 응용 때문에 특히 중요하다. 시간에 따라 변하는 deterministic optimization에 대해서는 non-parametric 접근법이 제안되어 왔지만, 그 stochastic counterpart를 위해서는 아직 고안되지 않았다. 본 연구는 Malliavin calculus에 기반한 stochastic variational framework를 개발함으로써 비모수적 optimality를 구체적으로 다룬다. 이 framework는 stochastic decision을 갖는 SO 문제에 대해 non-parametric optimality condition을 도출할 수 있게 하며, parameterization dimension에 둔감한 확장 가능한 deep-learning 알고리즘의 설계를 지원한다. stochastic path follower (SPF)라 불리는 이 알고리즘은 distribution drift 하에서의 두 핵심 문제, 즉 least-squares recovery와 logistic regression을 해결하는 데 적용된다. 실험 결과는 performance와 scalability 양쪽 모두에서 제안한 접근법이 최신 learning-based 및 gradient-based 방법보다 우수함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"64722","en":"Decision-focused Sparse Tangent Portfolio Optimization","ko":"의사결정 중심 Sparse Tangent Portfolio Optimization","authors":"Haeun Jeon, Seunghoon Choi, Hyunglip Bae, Yongjae Lee, Woo Chang Kim","pos":"#3701","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=KV7XHF0IbK","abs":"<p>Sparse tangent portfolio optimization aims to learn an interpretable, low-cardinality portfolio in the tangency direction of the mean–variance frontier, yet the associated cardinality-constrained formulation is NP-hard and standard predict-then-optimize pipelines often misalign forecasting accuracy with downstream portfolio quality. We propose an end-to-end decision-focused learning framework that reformulates Sharpe-ratio maximization as a Disciplined Parametrized Programming (DPP)-compliant convex programming layer and replaces discrete selection with a smooth top-k operator enforcing an exact sum-to-k sparsity budget. This enables gradient flow through prediction, asset selection, and re-optimization, allowing the predictive model to directly optimize the portfolio performance. Across five major equity markets, our method consistently delivers higher out-of-sample Sharpe ratios than historical and prediction-focused baselines while producing meaningful sparse selections.</p>","absKo":"<p>Sparse tangent portfolio optimization은 mean–variance frontier의 tangency direction에서 해석 가능하고 저카디널리티인 포트폴리오를 학습하는 것을 목표로 하지만, 이와 연관된 cardinality-constrained formulation은 NP-hard이며 표준 predict-then-optimize 파이프라인은 종종 예측 정확도와 downstream portfolio quality를 정렬하지 못합니다. 우리는 Sharpe ratio maximization을 Disciplined Parametrized Programming (DPP) 준수 convex programming layer로 재정식화하고, discrete selection을 정확한 sum-to-k sparsity budget을 강제하는 smooth top-k operator로 대체하는 end-to-end decision-focused learning framework를 제안합니다. 이를 통해 prediction, asset selection, re-optimization 전반에 걸쳐 gradient flow가 가능해지며, predictive model이 portfolio performance를 직접 최적화할 수 있습니다. 5개의 주요 equity market 전반에서, 우리의 방법은 일관되게 historical 및 prediction-focused baseline보다 더 높은 out-of-sample Sharpe ratio를 제공하면서 의미 있는 sparse selection을 생성합니다.</p>"},{"id":"63233","en":"Beyond the Bellman Recursion: A Pontryagin-Guided Framework for Non-Exponential Discounting","ko":"Bellman 재귀를 넘어서: 비지수 할인을 위한 Pontryagin 유도 프레임워크","authors":"Hojin Ko, Jeonggyu Huh","pos":"#3703","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Ys66H59k8m","abs":"<p>Most value-based and actor-critic reinforcement learning methods rely on Bellman-style recursions, yet these recursions collapse under non-exponential discounting common in human preferences and survival processes. We show the breakdown is structural: exponential discounting sits at a fragile intersection of multiplicativity and time homogeneity, and violating either property breaks standard dynamic programming. To overcome this, we propose <strong>Pontryagin-Guided Direct Policy Optimization (PG-DPO)</strong>, a variational framework that abandons recursion and couples the Pontryagin Maximum Principle with Monte Carlo rollouts via an <em>Adjoint-MC projection</em> enforcing pointwise Hamiltonian maximization. Across multidimensional hyperbolic and survival-discount benchmarks, PG-DPO improves accuracy and stability where equation-driven solvers and critic-based baselines diverge.</p>","absKo":"<p>대부분의 value-based 및 actor-critic reinforcement learning 방법은 Bellman-style recursion에 의존하지만, 이러한 recursion은 인간 선호와 생존 과정에서 흔한 non-exponential discounting 하에서는 붕괴한다. 우리는 그 붕괴가 구조적임을 보인다. exponential discounting은 multiplicativity와 time homogeneity의 취약한 교차점에 놓여 있으며, 어느 하나라도 위반하면 표준 dynamic programming이 깨진다. 이를 극복하기 위해, 우리는 recursion을 버리고 Pontryagin Maximum Principle과 Monte Carlo rollout을 <em>Adjoint-MC projection</em>으로 결합하여 pointwise Hamiltonian maximization을 강제하는 변분적 framework인 <strong>Pontryagin-Guided Direct Policy Optimization(PG-DPO)</strong>를 제안한다. 다차원 hyperbolic 및 survival-discount benchmark 전반에서, PG-DPO는 equation-driven solver와 critic-based baseline이 발산하는 상황에서도 정확도와 안정성을 향상시킨다.</p>"},{"id":"63104","en":"Why Do We Need Warm-up? A Theoretical Perspective","ko":"왜 Warm-up이 필요한가? 이론적 관점","authors":"Foivos Alimisis, Rustem Islamov, Aurelien Lucchi","pos":"#3704","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=a6fo32UnpU","abs":"Learning rate warm-up -- increasing the learning rate at the beginning of training -- has become a ubiquitous heuristic in modern deep learning, yet its theoretical foundations remain poorly understood. In this work, we provide a principled explanation for why warm-up improves training. We rely on a generalization of the $(L_0, L_1)$-smoothness condition, which bounds local curvature as a linear function of the loss sub-optimality and exhibits desirable closure properties. We show -- both theoretically and empirically -- that this condition is satisfied by common neural architectures and accurately captures the curvature of the optimization landscape early in training. Adapting the learning rate in response to this curvature condition naturally induces a warm-up–like schedule, and we show that this choice yields provably faster convergence guarantees than using a fixed learning rate. Finally, we validate our theoretical insights through experiments on language and vision models, confirming the agreement between our theoretically derived schedule and standard warm-up.","absKo":"학습률 warm-up -- 훈련 초기에 학습률을 증가시키는 것 -- 은 현대 딥러닝에서 어디서나 쓰이는 휴리스틱이 되었지만, 그 이론적 기반은 여전히 충분히 이해되지 않았다. 본 연구에서는 warm-up이 훈련을 개선하는 이유에 대한 원리적인 설명을 제시한다. 우리는 손실의 sub-optimality에 대한 선형 함수로 local curvature를 상한하는, 그리고 바람직한 closure property를 보이는 $(L_0, L_1)$-smoothness 조건의 일반화에 의존한다. 우리는 이 조건이 일반적인 neural architecture에서 만족됨을 이론적으로도, 실증적으로도 보이며, 훈련 초기에 optimization landscape의 curvature를 정확하게 포착함을 보인다. 이 curvature 조건에 따라 learning rate를 조정하면 자연스럽게 warm-up과 유사한 schedule이 유도되며, 이러한 선택이 고정 learning rate를 사용할 때보다 더 빠른 수렴을 보장함을 증명한다. 마지막으로, language 및 vision model에 대한 실험을 통해 이러한 이론적 통찰을 검증하고, 이론적으로 유도한 schedule과 표준 warm-up 사이의 일치를 확인한다."},{"id":"64199","en":"Hyperparameter Transfer Laws for Non-Recurrent Multi-Path Neural Networks","ko":"비순환 다중 경로 신경망을 위한 하이퍼파라미터 전이 법칙","authors":"Haosong Zhang, Shenxi Wu, Xingjian Ma, Shirui Bian, Yichi Zhang, Xi Chen, Wei Lin","pos":"#3705","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Q2tAR1xDFQ","abs":"Deeper modern architectures are costly to train, making hyperparameter transfer preferable to expensive repeated tuning. Maximal Update Parametrization ($\\mu$P) helps explain why many hyperparameters transfer across width. Yet depth scaling is less understood for modern architectures, whose computation graphs contain multiple parallel paths and residual aggregation. To unify various non-recurrent multi-path neural networks such as CNNs, ResNets, and Transformers, we introduce a graph-based notion of effective depth. Under stabilizing initializations and a maximal-update criterion, we show that the optimal learning rate decays with effective depth following a universal -3/2 power law. Here, the maximal-update criterion maximizes the typical one-step representation change at initialization without causing instability, and effective depth is the minimal path length from input to output, counting layers and residual additions. Experiments across diverse architectures confirm the predicted slope and enable reliable zero-shot transfer of learning rates across depths and widths, turning depth scaling into a predictable hyperparameter-transfer problem.","absKo":"더 깊은 modern architecture는 학습 비용이 크기 때문에, 반복적인 expensive tuning보다 hyperparameter transfer가 더 바람직하다. Maximal Update Parametrization ($\\mu$P)은 width에 걸쳐 많은 hyperparameter가 왜 transfer되는지 설명하는 데 도움을 준다. 그러나 depth scaling은 computation graph에 여러 parallel path와 residual aggregation이 포함된 modern architecture에서는 덜 이해되어 있다. CNN, ResNet, Transformer와 같은 다양한 non-recurrent multi-path neural network를 통합하기 위해, 우리는 graph-based 개념의 effective depth를 도입한다. 안정화된 initialization과 maximal-update criterion 하에서, optimal learning rate가 effective depth에 따라 보편적인 -3/2 power law를 따른다는 것을 보인다. 여기서 maximal-update criterion은 불안정을 유발하지 않으면서 initialization에서의 전형적인 one-step representation change를 최대화하며, effective depth는 layer와 residual addition을 세어 input에서 output까지의 최소 path length이다. 다양한 architecture에 대한 실험은 예측된 slope를 확인하며, depth와 width 전반에 걸친 learning rate의 reliable zero-shot transfer를 가능하게 하여, depth scaling을 예측 가능한 hyperparameter-transfer 문제로 바꾼다."},{"id":"64921","en":"From Muon to Gluon: Bridging Theory and Practice of LMO-based Optimizers for LLMs","ko":"Muon에서 Gluon으로: LLM을 위한 LMO 기반 Optimizer의 이론과 실제 연결","authors":"Artem Riabinin, Egor Shulgin, Kaja Gruntkowska, Peter Richtarik","pos":"#3706","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=IelAHU5MVz","abs":"<p>Recent developments in deep learning optimization have brought about radically new algorithms based on the Linear Minimization Oracle (LMO) framework, such as Muon and Scion. After over a decade of Adam's dominance, these LMO-based methods are emerging as viable replacements, offering several practical advantages such as improved memory efficiency, better hyperparameter transferability, and most importantly, superior empirical performance on large-scale tasks, including LLM training. However, a significant gap remains between their practical use and our current theoretical understanding: prior analyses (1) overlook the layer-wise LMO application of these optimizers in practice, and (2) rely on an unrealistic smoothness assumption, leading to impractically small stepsizes. To address both, we propose a new LMO-based framework called Gluon, capturing prior theoretically analyzed methods as special cases, and introduce a new refined generalized smoothness model that captures the layer-wise geometry of neural networks, matches the layer-wise practical implementation of Muon and Scion, and leads to state-of-the-art convergence guarantees. Our experiments with NanoGPT and CNN confirm that our assumption holds along the optimization trajectory, ultimately closing the gap between theory and practice.</p>"},{"id":"66779","en":"Constructing Industrial-Scale Optimization Modeling Benchmark","ko":"산업 규모 최적화 모델링 벤치마크 구축","authors":"Zhong Li, Hongliang Lu, Tao Wei, Wenyu Liu, Yuxuan Chen, Yuan LAN, Fan Zhang, Zaiwen Wen","pos":"#3800","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=0Q7adIsv6p","abs":"Optimization modeling underpins decision-making in logistics, manufacturing, energy, and finance, yet translating natural-language requirements into correct optimization formulations and solver-executable code remains labor-intensive. Although large language models (LLMs) have been explored for this task, evaluation is still dominated by toy-sized or synthetic benchmarks, masking the difficulty of industrial problems with $10^{3}$--$10^{6}$ (or more) variables and constraints. A key bottleneck is the lack of benchmarks that align natural-language specifications with reference formulations/solver code grounded in real optimization models. To fill in this gap, we introduce MIPLIB-NL, built via a structure-aware reverse construction methodology from real mixed-integer linear programs in MIPLIB~2017. Our pipeline (i) recovers compact, reusable model structure from flat solver formulations, (ii) reverse-generates natural-language specifications explicitly tied to this recovered structure under a unified model--data separation format, and (iii) performs iterative semantic validation through expert review and human--LLM interaction with independent reconstruction checks. This yields 223 one-to-one reconstructions that preserve the mathematical content of the original instances while enabling realistic natural-language-to-optimization evaluation. Experiments show substantial performance degradation on MIPLIB-NL for systems that perform strongly on existing benchmarks, exposing failure modes invisible at toy scale."},{"id":"63206","en":"Trainable Nonexpansive Denoisers for Contractive Image Reconstruction","ko":"수축적 이미지 재구성을 위한 학습 가능한 비확장 노이즈 제거기","authors":"Arghya Sinha, Aditya Banerjee, Trishit Mukherjee, Kunal Narayan Chaudhury","pos":"#3802","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Z6j8S5LWmL","abs":"Trainable denoisers with Lipschitz control have become central to convergent image reconstruction. However, training neural networks that simultaneously offer strong denoising performance and global Lipschitz guarantees is challenging. Existing approaches enforce Lipschitz control only empirically, providing no guarantees beyond the training data. In this work, we show that by exploiting the action of permutations on the image lattice, we can constrain a neural architecture that is globally nonexpansive (Lipschitz bound $\\leqslant 1$). We integrate the proposed denoiser with forward imaging operators to develop a reconstruction mechanism that is provably contractive and therefore globally convergent. Experiments on standard inverse problems, such as superresolution and deblurring, demonstrate that our reconstruction performance is competitive with softly constrained baselines while providing Lipschitz guarantees.","absKo":"Lipschitz control을 갖는 trainable denoiser는 수렴하는 image reconstruction의 핵심이 되었다. 그러나 강한 denoising 성능과 전역 Lipschitz 보장을 동시에 제공하는 neural network를 학습하는 것은 어렵다. 기존 방법은 Lipschitz control을 경험적으로만 강제할 뿐, training data를 넘어서는 보장을 제공하지 못한다. 본 연구에서는 이미지 lattice에 대한 permutation의 작용을 활용함으로써, 전역적으로 nonexpansive한(neural architecture의 Lipschitz bound $\\leqslant 1$) 구조를 제약할 수 있음을 보인다. 우리는 제안하는 denoiser를 forward imaging operator와 통합하여, provably contractive하며 따라서 전역적으로 수렴하는 reconstruction mechanism을 개발한다. superresolution과 deblurring 같은 표준 inverse problem에 대한 실험은, 부드럽게 제약된 baseline과 경쟁력 있는 reconstruction 성능을 보이면서도 Lipschitz 보장을 제공함을 보여준다."},{"id":"64727","en":"Complexity of Decentralized Optimization with Mixed Affine Constraints","ko":"혼합 Affine 제약을 가진 분산 최적화의 복잡도","authors":"Demyan Yarmoshik, Nhat Trung Nguyen, Alexander Rogozin, Alexander Gasnikov","pos":"#3807","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=KS6RbZMt8L","abs":"<p>This paper considers decentralized optimization of convex functions with mixed affine equality constraints involving both local and global variables. Constraints on global variables may vary across different nodes in the network, while local variables are subject to coupled and node-specific constraints. Such problem formulations arise in machine learning applications, including federated learning and multi-task learning, as well as in resource allocation and distributed control. We analyze this problem under smooth and non-smooth assumptions, considering both strongly convex and general convex objective functions. Our main contribution is an optimal algorithm for the smooth, strongly convex regime, whose convergence rate matches established lower complexity bounds. We further provide near-optimal methods for the remaining cases.</p>","absKo":"<p>이 논문은 local 변수와 global 변수를 모두 포함하는 mixed affine equality constraint 하에서 convex function의 decentralized optimization을 다룹니다. global 변수에 대한 제약은 네트워크의 서로 다른 node마다 달라질 수 있으며, local 변수는 coupled 및 node-specific constraint를 받습니다. 이러한 문제 설정은 federated learning과 multi-task learning을 포함한 machine learning 응용뿐 아니라 resource allocation과 distributed control에도 나타납니다. 우리는 이 문제를 smooth 및 non-smooth 가정 하에서 분석하며, strongly convex 및 general convex objective function을 모두 고려합니다. 우리의 주요 기여는 smooth하고 strongly convex한 regime에서의 optimal algorithm으로, 수렴률이 확립된 lower complexity bound와 일치합니다. 또한 나머지 경우들에 대해서는 near-optimal method를 제공합니다.</p>"},{"id":"63893","en":"Adapting to Evolving Graphs: A Scalable Framework for Dynamic Coarsening","ko":"진화하는 그래프에 적응하기: 동적 coarseening을 위한 확장 가능한 프레임워크","authors":"Abhishek Gupta, Manoj Kumar, Sarthak Singh, Ujjwal Yadav, Yifan Sun, Sandeep Kumar","pos":"#3900","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=SkgX7UTVdi","abs":"Graph coarsening is a fundamental dimensionality reduction technique for scaling large graphs while preserving structural and feature information. However, most existing coarsening methods are designed for static graphs and do not extend well to dynamic settings where nodes, edges, and connectivity patterns evolve over time. Recomputing a coarsened graph from scratch after every update is often infeasible, which limits scalability and real-time applicability. To address this, we propose a unified framework for coarsening discrete-time dynamic graphs by incrementally updating the coarsening mapping matrix. The framework initializes from any static coarsening technique and then efficiently incorporates real-world graph events, including node additions, node deletions, and edge modifications. We instantiate this framework with two optimization based incremental update algorithms tailored to different dynamic regimes, one focusing on efficiently integrating growth related changes and another handling broader topology evolution with adaptive reassignment. We derive fast and scalable solvers with convergence guarantees, and provide theoretical guarantee via $\\epsilon$-similarity bounds that quantify and control quality degradation in the coarsened graph. Extensive experiments under realistic dynamic scenarios show substantial improvements in runtime and memory, delivering significant speedups while maintaining or improving downstream task performance, including graph neural network accuracy.","absKo":"그래프 coarsening은 구조와 feature 정보를 보존하면서 대규모 그래프의 규모를 확장하기 위한 기본적인 차원 축소 기법이다. 그러나 기존의 대부분 coarsening 방법은 정적 그래프를 위해 설계되어 있으며, 노드, 엣지, 연결 패턴이 시간에 따라 변하는 동적 설정에는 잘 확장되지 않는다. 각 업데이트마다 coarsened graph를 처음부터 다시 계산하는 것은 종종 비현실적이어서, 확장성과 실시간 적용 가능성이 제한된다. 이를 해결하기 위해 우리는 coarsening mapping matrix를 점진적으로 업데이트하는 방식으로 discrete-time dynamic graph를 coarsening하기 위한 통합 프레임워크를 제안한다. 이 프레임워크는 어떤 static coarsening technique에서도 초기화할 수 있으며, 이후 node 추가, node 삭제, edge 수정 등 실제 그래프 이벤트를 효율적으로 반영한다. 우리는 이 프레임워크를 두 가지 optimization-based incremental update algorithm으로 구체화했으며, 하나는 성장 관련 변화를 효율적으로 통합하는 데 중점을 두고, 다른 하나는 adaptive reassignment를 통해 보다 폭넓은 topology 진화를 처리한다. 우리는 수렴 보장을 갖는 빠르고 확장 가능한 solver를 도출하고, coarsened graph에서 품질 저하를 정량화하고 제어하는 $\\epsilon$-similarity bound를 통해 이론적 보장을 제공한다. 현실적인 동적 시나리오에서 수행한 대규모 실험은 runtime과 memory에서 상당한 개선을 보였고, graph neural network 정확도를 포함한 downstream task 성능을 유지하거나 향상시키면서 의미 있는 속도 향상을 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"62165","en":"Mirror Descent Under Generalized Smoothness","ko":"일반화된 Smoothness 하의 Mirror Descent","authors":"Dingzhi Yu, Wei Jiang, Hongyi Tao, Yuanyu Wan, Lijun Zhang","pos":"#3904","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=j9aoIFr5aM","abs":"Smoothness is crucial for attaining fast rates in first-order optimization. However, many optimization problems in modern machine learning involve non-smooth objectives. Recent studies relax the smoothness assumption by allowing the Lipschitz constant of the gradient to grow with respect to the gradient norm, which accommodates a broad range of objectives in practice. Despite this progress, existing generalizations of smoothness are restricted to Euclidean geometry with $\\ell_2$-norm and only have theoretical guarantees for optimization in the Euclidean space. In this paper, we address this limitation by introducing a new $\\ell*$-smoothness concept that measures the norm of Hessians in terms of a general norm and its dual, and establish convergence for mirror-descent-type algorithms, matching the rates under the classic smoothness. Notably, we propose a generalized self-bounding property that facilitates bounding the gradients via controlling suboptimality gaps, serving as a principal component for convergence analysis. Beyond deterministic optimization, we establish sharp convergence for stochastic mirror descent, matching state-of-the-art under classic smoothness. Our theory also extends to non-convex and composite optimization, which may shed light on practical usages of mirror descent, including pre-training and post-training of LLMs.","absKo":"Smoothness는 first-order optimization에서 빠른 rate를 달성하는 데 핵심적이다. 그러나 현대 machine learning의 많은 optimization problem은 non-smooth objective를 포함한다. 최근 연구들은 gradient norm에 따라 gradient의 Lipschitz constant가 증가하도록 허용함으로써 smoothness 가정을 완화했고, 이는 실무에서 폭넓은 objective를 포괄한다. 이러한 진전에도 불구하고, 기존의 smoothness 일반화는 $\\ell_2$-norm을 사용하는 Euclidean geometry에 제한되어 있으며, Euclidean space에서의 optimization에 대해서만 이론적 보장을 제공한다. 본 논문에서는 일반 norm과 그 dual을 사용하여 Hessian의 norm을 측정하는 새로운 $\\ell*$-smoothness 개념을 도입하여 이 한계를 해결하고, classic smoothness 하에서의 rate와 일치하는 mirror-descent-type algorithm의 수렴을 확립한다. 특히, 우리는 suboptimality gap을 제어함으로써 gradient를 bound하는 데 유용한 generalized self-bounding property를 제안하며, 이는 수렴 분석의 핵심 구성요소로 작동한다. deterministic optimization을 넘어, 우리는 stochastic mirror descent에 대해서도 sharp convergence를 확립하여 classic smoothness 하의 state-of-the-art와 일치하는 결과를 얻는다. 우리의 이론은 non-convex 및 composite optimization으로도 확장되며, pre-training과 post-training을 포함한 LLM의 mirror descent 실용 활용에 대한 통찰을 제공할 수 있다."},{"id":"66478","en":"Lower Bounds for Frank-Wolfe on Strongly Convex Sets","ko":"강볼록 집합에서 Frank-Wolfe의 하한","authors":"Jannis Halbey, Daniel Deza, Max Zimmer, Christophe Roux, Bartolomeo Stellato, Sebastian Pokutta","pos":"#3905","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=3KX1xU2bCC","abs":"We present a constructive lower bound of $\\Omega(1/\\sqrt{\\varepsilon})$ for Frank-Wolfe (FW) when both the objective and the constraint set are smooth and strongly convex, showing that the known uniform $\\mathcal{O}(1/\\sqrt{\\varepsilon})$ guarantees in this regime are tight. It is known that under additional assumptions on the position of the optimizer, FW can converge linearly. However, it remained unclear whether strong convexity of the set can yield rates \\emph{uniformly} faster than $\\mathcal{O}(1/\\sqrt{\\varepsilon})$, i.e., irrespective of the position of the optimizer. To investigate this question, we focus on a simple yet representative problem class: minimizing a strongly convex quadratic over the Euclidean unit ball, with the optimizer on the boundary. We analyze the dynamics of FW for this problem in detail and develop a novel computational approach to construct worst-case FW trajectories, which is of independent interest. Guided by these constructions, we develop an analytical proof establishing the lower bound."},{"id":"64648","en":"Design Linear Constrained Neural Layers with Implicit Convex Optimization","ko":"Implicit Convex Optimization을 활용한 선형 제약 신경망 계층 설계","authors":"Junchi Yan, Liangliang Shi, Jiaxi Liu, Fangyuan Zhou, Wenzheng Pan, Zhongteng Gui, Yihui Tu","pos":"#3906","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=LHCQSx0cQV","abs":"<p>One essential limitation of neural networks is how to enforce (hard) constraints on prediction. We propose a plug-in, differentiable layer, which involves a fast implicit (convex) optimization procedure to enforce the general linear constraint. It aims to minimize a divergence between unconstrained and constrained outputs. Connecting to and beyond existing handcrafted layers, we show that our layer degrades to classic layers like Softmax, Sinkhorn and tanh etc. when the corresponding constraint is enforced by KL-divergence minimization. We further show that by replacing the KL-div with a Euclidean distance, a closed-form solution can be derived for highly-efficient constraint enforcing. We evaluate the above two variants of layers, termed as BLCLayer and GLCLayer, with their corresponding neural solver BLCNet and GLCNet with simple MLP/GNN-like backbone. Experiments on linear programming, as well as two real-world problems: partial graph matching and portfolio allocation which involve other discrete constraints.</p>","absKo":"<p>신경망의 본질적 한계 중 하나는 prediction에 대해 (hard) constraint를 어떻게 강제할 것인가이다. 우리는 일반적인 linear constraint를 강제하기 위해 빠른 implicit (convex) optimization 절차를 포함하는 plug-in 형태의 differentiable layer를 제안한다. 이 layer는 unconstrained output과 constrained output 사이의 divergence를 최소화하는 것을 목표로 한다. 기존의 handcrafted layer들과 연결해 보면, 해당 constraint가 KL-divergence minimization으로 강제될 때 이 layer는 Softmax, Sinkhorn, tanh 등과 같은 고전적 layer로 퇴화함을 보인다. 또한 KL-div를 Euclidean distance로 대체하면, 매우 효율적인 constraint enforcement를 위한 closed-form solution을 도출할 수 있음을 보인다. 우리는 이 두 변형을 각각 BLCLayer와 GLCLayer라 부르고, 그에 대응하는 neural solver인 BLCNet과 GLCNet을 단순한 MLP/GNN-like backbone과 함께 평가한다. 실험은 linear programming뿐 아니라, 다른 discrete constraint를 포함하는 두 가지 실제 문제인 partial graph matching과 portfolio allocation에서도 수행했다.</p>"},{"id":"63194","en":"Decision-Focused Learning via Tangent-Space Projection of Prediction Error","ko":"예측 오차의 접공간 사영을 통한 결정 중심 학습","authors":"Junhyeong Lee, Sangjin Jin, Yongjae Lee","pos":"#3907","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ZDtFevjwin","abs":"<p>Decision-Focused Learning (DFL) trains predictors to improve downstream decision quality, but computing regret gradients typically requires differentiating through solvers or relying on surrogate losses, which can be computationally expensive or deviate from the true objective. We show that, under standard regularity with locally stable active constraints, the regret gradient admits a closed-form geometric characterization, equivalent to the prediction error projected onto the tangent space of active constraints, scaled by lo- cal curvature. This reveals that regret gradients can be obtained by filtering decision-irrelevant components from the MSE gradient, providing a simpler and more direct alternative to existing approaches. Based on this, we propose PEAR (Projected Error As Regret-gradient), which computes regret gradients via a reduced linear system over active constraints, avoiding differentiation through solver iterations or additional optimization solves. Experiments on LP benchmarks and a real-world QP task show that PEAR achieves the best decision quality among all baselines while being the most computationally efficient, with gains that persist under constraint shifts.</p>","absKo":"<p>Decision-Focused Learning(DFL)은 predictor를 훈련해 downstream decision quality를 향상시키지만, regret gradient를 계산하려면 보통 solver를 미분해야 하거나 surrogate loss에 의존해야 하므로 계산 비용이 크거나 진짜 objective에서 벗어날 수 있다. 우리는 표준 regularity와 locally stable active constraint 하에서 regret gradient가 닫힌형 기하학적 특성화를 갖는다는 것을 보인다. 이는 prediction error가 active constraint의 tangent space로 projection된 뒤 local curvature로 스케일된 것과 동등하다. 이는 regret gradient가 MSE gradient에서 decision-irrelevant component를 필터링해 얻어질 수 있음을 보여주며, 기존 접근법보다 더 단순하고 직접적인 대안을 제공한다. 이를 바탕으로 우리는 PEAR(Projected Error As Regret-gradient)를 제안한다. PEAR는 active constraint에 대한 축소된 linear system을 통해 regret gradient를 계산하여 solver iteration을 미분하거나 추가 optimization solve를 수행하지 않는다. LP benchmark와 실제 QP task에 대한 실험은 PEAR가 모든 baseline 중 가장 좋은 decision quality를 달성하면서도 가장 계산적으로 효율적이며, constraint shift가 있어도 그 이점이 유지됨을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"64813","en":"Adaptive Momentum and Nonlinear Damping for Neural Network Training","ko":"신경망 학습을 위한 적응적 Momentum과 비선형 Damping","authors":"Aikaterini Karoni, Rajit Rajpal, Benedict Leimkuhler, Gabriel Stoltz","pos":"#3908","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=JWWpV4StVf","abs":"<p>Momentum Stochastic Gradient Descent (mSGD) relies on a fixed momentum coefficient shared across all parameters, failing to account for the heterogeneous structure of modern loss landscapes. In this work, we adopt a continuous-time formulation to introduce individual, adaptive momentum coefficients regulated by the kinetic energy of each model parameter. This mechanism automatically adjusts to local curvature to maintain stability without sacrificing convergence speed. We demonstrate that this adaptive friction is inextricably linked to cubic damping, a suppression mechanism from structural dynamics. We additionally introduce two optimization schemes by augmenting the continuous dynamics of mSGD and Adam with a cubic damping term. Empirically, our methods demonstrate robustness and match or outperform Adam on training ViT, BERT, and GPT2; tasks where mSGD typically struggles. We further provide theoretical results establishing the exponential convergence of the proposed schemes.</p>"},{"id":"63794","en":"Rethinking Neural Network Learning Rates: A Stackelberg Perspective","ko":"신경망 학습률 재고: Stackelberg 관점","authors":"Sihan Zeng, Sujay Bhatt, Sumitra Ganesh","pos":"#4505","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=TgohCXoblV","abs":"<p>Neural networks are typically trained with a single learning rate across all layers. While recent empirical evidence suggests that assigning layer-specific learning rates can accelerate training, a principled understanding of the conditions and mechanisms under which non-uniform learning rates are beneficial remains limited. In this work, we investigate non-uniform learning rates through the lens of Stackelberg optimization. Specifically, we demonstrate that training neural networks with a smaller learning rate for the body layers and a larger learning rate for the final layer can be interpreted as a two-time-scale alternating gradient descent algorithm applied to a Stackelberg reformulation of the original objective. We establish finite-time convergence guarantees for the algorithm under broad conditions that accommodate constraint sets and non-smooth activation functions. Beyond convergence, we identify two mechanisms by which non-uniform learning rates can outperform uniform learning rates: (i) we show that certain problem instances induce a Stackelberg objective with stronger optimization structure than the original objective, yielding faster convergence to globally optimal solutions, (ii) our numerical analysis reveals that the Stackelberg objective can exhibit substantially sharper local curvature, especially in early training, which leads to more informative gradients and learning acceleration. Experiments in supervised learning and reinforcement learning support our findings.</p>","absKo":"<p>Neural network는 일반적으로 모든 layer에 대해 동일한 learning rate로 학습된다. 최근의 실증적 증거는 layer별 learning rate를 부여하면 학습을 가속할 수 있음을 시사하지만, 비균일 learning rate가 유익한 조건과 메커니즘에 대한 원리적 이해는 여전히 제한적이다. 본 연구에서는 Stackelberg optimization의 관점에서 비균일 learning rate를 조사한다. 구체적으로, body layer에는 더 작은 learning rate를, 마지막 layer에는 더 큰 learning rate를 사용해 neural network를 학습하는 것이 원래 objective의 Stackelberg reformulation에 적용된 two-time-scale alternating gradient descent algorithm으로 해석될 수 있음을 보인다. 우리는 constraint set과 non-smooth activation function을 포괄하는 광범위한 조건 하에서 이 algorithm의 finite-time convergence 보장을 확립한다. 수렴을 넘어, 우리는 비균일 learning rate가 균일 learning rate를 능가할 수 있는 두 가지 메커니즘을 식별한다. (i) 특정 문제 인스턴스가 원래 objective보다 더 강한 optimization structure를 지닌 Stackelberg objective를 유도하여 전역 최적해로의 더 빠른 수렴을 가능하게 함을 보인다. (ii) 우리의 수치 분석은 특히 학습 초기 단계에서 Stackelberg objective가 훨씬 더 날카로운 local curvature를 보일 수 있으며, 이는 더 정보성 있는 gradient와 학습 가속으로 이어짐을 밝힌다. 지도학습과 reinforcement learning 실험은 이러한 발견을 뒷받침한다.</p>"},{"id":"63117","en":"FOAM: Frequency and Operator-Error Based Adaptive Damping Method for Reducing Staleness-Oriented Error for Shampoo","ko":"FOAM: Shampoo의 진부화 지향 오차 감소를 위한 주파수 및 연산자 오차 기반 적응형 감쇠 방법","authors":"Kyunghun Nam, Sumyeong Ahn","pos":"#4507","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ZwFJbTzJP9","abs":"<p>Shampoo is attracting considerable attention for its superior performance on large-scale optimization benchmarks; yet it faces a significant practical bottleneck: the prohibitive computational overhead of matrix inversion. To mitigate this, practitioners typically rely on stale preconditioner updates, creating a fundamental trade-off between computational efficiency and optimization fidelity. In this work, we provide a theoretical study of staleness through the complementary lenses of convergence and stability. While staleness improves computational efficiency, it inherently degrades performance and introduces numerical instability. Guided by this analysis, we propose FOAM, an adaptive algorithm that stabilizes training by dynamically controlling both the damping factor and the eigendecomposition frequency based on an approximation of the staleness-oriented error. Experimental results demonstrate that FOAM reduces wall-clock time compared to standard Shampoo while maintaining robust convergence.</p>","absKo":"<p>Shampoo는 대규모 optimization benchmark에서 우수한 성능으로 큰 주목을 받고 있지만, matrix inversion의 과도한 계산 오버헤드라는 심각한 실용적 병목을 안고 있다. 이를 완화하기 위해 실무에서는 일반적으로 stale preconditioner update에 의존하며, 이는 계산 효율성과 optimization fidelity 사이의 근본적인 trade-off를 만든다. 본 연구에서는 convergence와 stability라는 상보적인 관점에서 staleness를 이론적으로 분석한다. staleness는 계산 효율을 높이지만, 본질적으로 성능을 저하시키고 수치적 불안정성을 유발한다. 이러한 분석을 바탕으로, 우리는 staleness-oriented error의 근사치를 이용해 damping factor와 eigendecomposition frequency를 동적으로 제어함으로써 training을 안정화하는 adaptive algorithm FOAM을 제안한다. 실험 결과는 FOAM이 표준 Shampoo보다 wall-clock time을 줄이면서도 견고한 convergence를 유지함을 보여 준다.</p>"},{"id":"63171","en":"Preference-Modulated Structural Attention for Multi-Objective Combinatorial Optimization","ko":"다목적 조합 최적화를 위한 선호도 변조 구조적 어텐션","authors":"Rongsheng Jia, Yifan Zhang, Jun Zhang, Jian Cheng","pos":"#3901","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ZQ06bnxW2u","abs":"<p>Recent decomposition-based approaches have achieved significant success in Multi-Objective Combinatorial Optimization (MOCO). However,existing methods typically rely exclusively on node-centric representations, failing to capture the complementary representations provided by edge features for problem instances, resulting in a persistent optimality gap. To address this , we propose a Preference-Modulated Structural Attention mechanism to enhance problem representation by synergizing node and edge features. It includes: (1) Utilizing preference-modulated edge features as explicit structural biases during attention calculation, enabling model to perceive sub-problem structures conditioned on specific preferences,and (2) an edge feature aggregation strategy that dynamically incorporates node-specific context into edge representations to enhance the perception of preference-aware structures.  Experiments on classic MOCOP benchmarks demonstrate the superiority of our approach in terms of both performance and generalization capabilities.</p>","absKo":"<p>최근 decomposition-based approach는 Multi-Objective Combinatorial Optimization(MOCO)에서 큰 성공을 거두었다. 그러나 기존 방법은 일반적으로 node-centric representation에만 의존하여, 문제 인스턴스에 대해 edge feature가 제공하는 상보적 표현을 포착하지 못하고, 그 결과 지속적인 optimality gap이 발생한다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 node와 edge feature를 시너지 있게 결합하여 문제 표현을 강화하는 Preference-Modulated Structural Attention mechanism을 제안한다. 이는 다음을 포함한다: (1) preference-modulated edge feature를 attention 계산 시 explicit structural bias로 활용하여, 모델이 특정 preference에 조건화된 sub-problem structure를 인식할 수 있게 하는 것, 그리고 (2) node-specific context를 edge representation에 동적으로 통합하여 preference-aware structure에 대한 인식을 강화하는 edge feature aggregation strategy이다. 고전적인 MOCOP benchmark에서의 실험은 성능과 generalization capability 모두에서 우리의 접근법이 우수함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"64237","en":"Optimal Transport–Guided Stochastic Control for Graph Combinatorial Optimization","ko":"그래프 조합 최적화를 위한 최적 수송 유도 확률적 제어","authors":"Yang Huang, Yifan Zhang, Jian Cheng","pos":"#3902","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Pf2erYy0yY","abs":"<p>We propose an OT-guided sampling framework for solving graph combinatorial optimization through exact multilinear relaxation. Graph combinatorial optimization problems can be written as quadratic unconstrained binary optimization(QUBO). Leveraging a classical result in combinatorial optimization, we obtain a continuous multi-linear relaxation of QUBO that is exact, in the sense that it preserves the optimal binary solutions. The challenge is that the resulting energy landscape is highly nonconvex. We address this by treating the objective as an energy function and optimizing via sampling from the induced Boltzmann distribution to escape poor local optima. Viewing sampling as transporting a simple reference distribution to the target distribution, we use optimal transport to characterize more efficient probability flow and derive a stochastic optimal control problem whose solution yields an optimal sampling dynamics. We parameterize the control policy with graph neural networks to approximate the optimal control. Experiments show improved solution quality and efficiency over strong combinatorial and learning-based baselines.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 exact multilinear relaxation을 통해 graph combinatorial optimization을 해결하기 위한 OT-guided sampling framework를 제안한다. Graph combinatorial optimization 문제는 quadratic unconstrained binary optimization(QUBO)으로 쓸 수 있다. combinatorial optimization의 고전적 결과를 활용하여, 우리는 최적의 binary solution을 보존한다는 의미에서 exact한 QUBO의 continuous multi-linear relaxation을 얻는다. 문제는 그 결과 생기는 energy landscape가 매우 nonconvex하다는 점이다. 우리는 목적함수를 energy function으로 간주하고, 좋지 않은 local optimum을 벗어나기 위해 유도된 Boltzmann distribution에서 sampling하여 최적화한다. Sampling을 단순한 reference distribution을 target distribution으로 transport하는 과정으로 바라보고, 더 효율적인 probability flow를 특성화하기 위해 optimal transport를 사용하며, 그 해가 최적의 sampling dynamics를 산출하는 stochastic optimal control problem을 유도한다. 우리는 최적 control을 근사하기 위해 graph neural network로 control policy를 parameterize한다. 실험은 강력한 combinatorial 및 learning-based baseline들보다 향상된 solution quality와 효율성을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"67042","en":"Position: LLM Serving Needs Mathematical Optimization and Algorithmic Foundations, Not Just Heuristics","ko":"Position: LLM 서빙에는 휴리스틱만이 아니라 수학적 최적화와 알고리즘적 기초가 필요하다","authors":"Zijie Zhou","pos":"#1901","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ycj3XWCh6E","abs":"<p>This position paper argues that LLM inference serving has outgrown generic heuristics and now demands mathematical optimization and algorithmic foundations. Despite rapid advances in serving systems such as vLLM and SGLang, their algorithmic cores remain largely unchanged from classical distributed computing: request routing uses join-shortest-queue or round-robin, scheduling defaults to FIFO, and KV cache eviction follows LRU. These general-purpose policies ignore the distinctive structure of LLM inference—dynamically growing KV cache memory, prefill-decode phase asymmetry, unknown output lengths, and continuous batching constraints. We contend that the field must develop mathematical models capturing these characteristics, enabling the design of algorithms with provable performance guarantees across diverse workloads, rather than heuristics that may succeed in some scenarios but fail unpredictably in others. Emerging work at the intersection of operations research and ML systems demonstrates that principled methods can match or exceed heuristic performance while providing theoretical guarantees. We call on the community to recognize algorithmic design for LLM serving as a research frontier.</p>"},{"id":"63108","en":"Online Linear Programming for Multi-Objective Routing in LLM Serving","ko":"LLM 서빙에서 다목적 라우팅을 위한 온라인 선형 계획법","authors":"Zixi Chen, Yinyu Ye, Zijie Zhou","pos":"#1905","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=a51bLzOy1u","abs":"<p>We study the online routing problem in large language model serving, where requests arrive sequentially and must be dispatched to parallel decode workers under tight batch-size and KV-cache constraints. Unlike widely used routing heuristics that are not tied to explicit service-level objectives (SLOs) and offer limited control over latency–throughput trade-offs, we introduce an multi-objective optimization framework that formulates routing as an online linear programming with interpretable decision rewards. We apply an efficient bid-price control policy based on the online linear programming that admits requests when their SLO-weighted benefit exceeds their shadow prices. To meet millisecond decision requirements, we develop a warm-started, projected first-order updates that track the evolving dual shadow prices online with predictable runtime. We integrate our router into the Vidur simulator and demonstrate substantial improvements over standard baselines across multiple SLO regimes, including end-to-end latency, time-to-first-token, throughput, and tail performance. A big picture from our result: a science-based approach outperforms others based on heuristics.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 large language model serving에서의 online routing 문제를 연구한다. 여기서 요청은 순차적으로 도착하며, 엄격한 batch-size 및 KV-cache 제약 하에서 parallel decode worker에 할당되어야 한다. 명시적인 service-level objective (SLO)와 연결되어 있지 않고 latency–throughput trade-off에 대한 제어가 제한적인 널리 사용되는 routing heuristic과 달리, 우리는 해석 가능한 decision reward를 갖는 online linear programming으로 routing을 정식화하는 multi-objective optimization framework를 제안한다. 우리는 요청의 SLO-weighted benefit이 shadow price를 초과할 때 요청을 수락하는 online linear programming 기반의 효율적인 bid-price control policy를 적용한다. 밀리초 단위의 의사결정 요구를 충족하기 위해, 우리는 예측 가능한 runtime으로 진화하는 dual shadow price를 온라인에서 추적하는 warm-started, projected first-order update를 개발한다. 우리는 이 router를 Vidur simulator에 통합하고, end-to-end latency, time-to-first-token, throughput, tail performance를 포함한 여러 SLO regime에서 표준 baseline 대비 상당한 개선을 보인다. 우리의 결과가 주는 큰 그림은, 과학 기반 접근이 휴리스틱 기반 접근보다 더 우수하다는 점이다.</p>"},{"id":"61663","en":"UB-SMoE: Universally Balanced Sparse Mixture-of-Experts for Resource-adaptive Federated Fine-tuning of Foundation Models","ko":"UB-SMoE: Foundation Model의 자원 적응형 Federated Fine-tuning을 위한 Universally Balanced Sparse Mixture-of-Experts","authors":"Van-Tuan Tran, Hong-Hanh Nguyen-Le, Merim Dzaferagic, Marco Ruffini","pos":"#2806","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=nxgmp4aWer","abs":"Heterogeneous LoRA-rank methods address system heterogeneity in federated fine-tuning of foundation models by assigning client-specific ranks based on computational capabilities. However, these methods achieve only marginal computational savings, as dense feed-forward computations dominate. Sparse Mixture-of-Experts (SMoE) provides a promising alternative through conditional computation, yet we identify that its naive application to heterogeneous federated settings introduces two critical discordances: (i) expert utilization imbalance and (ii) non-differentiability of Top-K routing. Our convergence analysis demonstrates that these discordances lead to degraded convergence, particularly for resource-constrained clients. To address these challenges, we propose Universally Balanced Sparse Mixture-of-Experts (UB-SMoE), which introduces Dynamic Modulated Routing (DMR) to rebalance expert utilization, and Universal Pseudo-Gradient (PG) to reconstruct learning signals for non-activated experts. These mechanisms form a self-reinforcing cycle that maintains expert viability across heterogeneous clients. Experiments on benchmarks show that UB-SMoE achieves up to $45.0\\%$ computational reduction on low-resource clients while improving their performance by $8.7 \\times$ compared to existing heterogeneous LoRA-rank methods.","absKo":"Heterogeneous LoRA-rank methods는 연산 능력에 따라 client-specific rank를 할당함으로써 foundation model의 federated fine-tuning에서 시스템 이질성을 해결합니다. 그러나 dense feed-forward computation이 지배적이기 때문에 이러한 방법이 달성하는 계산 절감은 제한적입니다. Sparse Mixture-of-Experts (SMoE)는 conditional computation을 통해 유망한 대안이 되지만, 우리는 heterogeneous federated setting에 이를 단순 적용할 경우 두 가지 중대한 불일치가 발생함을 확인했습니다. (i) expert utilization imbalance, (ii) Top-K routing의 non-differentiability. 우리의 convergence analysis는 이러한 불일치가 특히 자원이 제한된 client에서 수렴 성능을 저하시킴을 보여줍니다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 expert utilization을 재균형화하는 Dynamic Modulated Routing (DMR)과, 활성화되지 않은 expert에 대한 학습 신호를 재구성하는 Universal Pseudo-Gradient (PG)를 도입한 Universally Balanced Sparse Mixture-of-Experts (UB-SMoE)를 제안합니다. 이러한 메커니즘은 heterogeneous client 전반에서 expert의 가용성을 유지하는 자기강화적 순환을 형성합니다. benchmark 실험 결과, UB-SMoE는 저자원 client에서 최대 $45.0\\%$의 계산 감소를 달성하는 동시에, 기존 heterogeneous LoRA-rank methods 대비 성능을 $8.7 \\times$ 향상시킵니다."},{"id":"67061","en":"Position: Federated Learning is a Lens towards a Democratized Future for the Scaling Law Era","ko":"Position: Federated Learning은 Scaling Law 시대의 민주화된 미래를 향한 렌즈이다","authors":"Harry Jiang, Baris Askin, Gauri Joshi, Carlee Joe-Wong","pos":"#3308","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=td1fQFeIiI","abs":"<p>Machine learning (ML) systems have grown significantly in size and popularity over recent years. However, the data and computation power supply chains which have helped fuel this growth have not been built without controversy. In particular, some of the data used to train these models may have been used without permission, while the growing appetite for compute power in model training increasingly incentivizes consolidation of access to larger players. As some stakeholders, such as data owners and everyday consumers of the Internet, have felt left behind by the emerging ML ecosystem, we seek to use federated learning paradigm as a model and motivation to develop a more democratized future for the ML community: one that is more decentralized, cooperative, and accountable. This position paper argues that the original proposition of federated learning as a framework enabling cooperation, privacy, and decentralization is still relevant today, even after the emergence of large foundation model- and scaling law-driven ML research, and that FL can inspire alternative ML ecosystems which alleviate and avoid the current frictions of large ML systems.</p>"},{"id":"62737","en":"One-Step Gradient Delay is Not a Barrier for Large-Scale Asynchronous Pipeline Parallel LLM Pretraining","ko":"One-Step Gradient Delay는 대규모 비동기 파이프라인 병렬 LLM 사전학습의 장벽이 아니다","authors":"Philip Zmushko, Egor Petrov, Nursultan Abdullaev, Khrushchev Mikhail, Samuel Horváth","pos":"#3610","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=dpWXlBRLKm","abs":"<p>Modern large-scale LLM pretraining benefits from utilizing Pipeline Parallelism; however, synchronous implementations leave GPUs idle during pipeline bubbles, wasting computational resources. Asynchronous Pipeline Parallelism approaches effectively eliminate these bubbles, maximizing throughput at the cost of gradient staleness. Unlike other schemes, PipeDream-2BW ensures a constant one-step gradient delay regardless of pipeline depth. However, its widespread adoption remains limited due to the common belief that optimizing under staleness is fundamentally unstable. In this work, we challenge this assumption, demonstrating that convergence degradation is largely an artifact of optimizer choice rather than an intrinsic limitation. We provide the first comprehensive analysis showing that while AdamW, the predominant optimizer at the time when PipeDream-2BW was introduced, indeed suffers from severe degradation, recent methods like Muon exhibit inherent robustness under a one step delay. We support this with theoretical analysis and introduce an optimizer-agnostic Error-Feedback mechanism to further mitigate delay effects. Extensive evaluation on models up to 10B parameters confirms that our strategies bridge the performance gap with synchronous training, enabling the practical deployment of asynchronous pipeline parallelism at scale.</p>","absKo":"<p>현대의 대규모 LLM pretraining은 Pipeline Parallelism을 활용할 때 이점을 얻지만, synchronous implementation은 pipeline bubble 동안 GPU를 유휴 상태로 남겨 computational resource를 낭비한다. Asynchronous Pipeline Parallelism 접근법은 이러한 bubble을 효과적으로 제거하여 gradient staleness를 감수하는 대신 throughput을 극대화한다. 다른 scheme과 달리 PipeDream-2BW는 pipeline depth와 무관하게 항상 한 step의 gradient delay를 보장한다. 그러나 staleness 하에서의 최적화가 근본적으로 불안정하다는 일반적인 인식 때문에, 그 광범위한 채택은 여전히 제한적이다. 본 연구에서는 이러한 가정에 도전하며, convergence degradation이 본질적 한계라기보다 optimizer 선택에 크게 기인함을 보인다. 우리는 PipeDream-2BW가 제안되던 당시 지배적이었던 optimizer인 AdamW는 실제로 심각한 degradation을 겪는 반면, Muon과 같은 최근 방법은 one step delay 하에서 본질적인 robustness를 보인다는 첫 포괄적 분석을 제시한다. 이를 이론적으로 분석하고, delay 효과를 추가로 완화하기 위해 optimizer-agnostic Error-Feedback mechanism을 도입한다. 최대 10B parameter 규모의 model에 대한 광범위한 평가를 통해, 우리의 전략이 synchronous training과의 성능 격차를 메우며 대규모에서 asynchronous pipeline parallelism을 실용적으로 배치할 수 있음을 확인한다.</p>"},{"id":"64430","en":"scDataset: Scalable Data Loading for Deep Learning on Large-Scale Single-Cell Omics","ko":"scDataset: 대규모 단일세포 오믹스에 대한 딥러닝을 위한 확장 가능한 데이터 로딩","authors":"Davide DAscenzo, Sebastiano Cultrera di Montesano","pos":"#3707","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=NiqWdmrxwn","abs":"<p>Training deep learning models on single-cell datasets with hundreds of millions of cells requires loading data from disk, as these datasets exceed available memory. While random sampling provides the data diversity needed for effective training, it is prohibitively slow due to the random access pattern overhead, whereas sequential streaming achieves high throughput but introduces biases that degrade model performance. We present scDataset, a PyTorch data loader that enables efficient training from on-disk data with seamless integration across diverse storage formats. Our approach combines block sampling and batched fetching to achieve quasi-random sampling that balances I/O efficiency with minibatch diversity. On Tahoe-100M, a dataset of 100 million cells, scDataset achieves more than two orders of magnitude speedup compared to true random sampling while working directly with AnnData files. We provide theoretical bounds on minibatch diversity and empirically show that scDataset matches the performance of true random sampling across multiple classification tasks.</p>","absKo":"수억 개의 cell로 이루어진 single-cell dataset에서 deep learning model을 학습하려면, 이러한 dataset이 사용 가능한 memory를 초과하기 때문에 disk에서 데이터를 불러와야 한다. Random sampling은 효과적인 학습에 필요한 data diversity를 제공하지만, random access pattern overhead 때문에 지나치게 느리다. 반면 sequential streaming은 높은 throughput을 달성하지만, model performance를 저하시키는 bias를 도입한다. 우리는 다양한 storage format에 걸쳐 매끄럽게 통합되는 on-disk data로부터 효율적인 학습을 가능하게 하는 PyTorch data loader인 scDataset을 제안한다. 우리의 접근법은 block sampling과 batched fetching을 결합하여 I/O efficiency와 minibatch diversity 사이의 균형을 맞추는 quasi-random sampling을 달성한다. 1억 개의 cell로 이루어진 Tahoe-100M dataset에서 scDataset은 AnnData file을 직접 사용하면서 true random sampling보다 100배가 넘는 speedup을 달성한다. 우리는 minibatch diversity에 대한 이론적 bound를 제시하고, scDataset이 여러 classification task에서 true random sampling과 동등한 성능을 보임을 실험적으로 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"62000","en":"ScaleSim: Serving Large-Scale Multi-Agent Simulation with Invocation Distance-Based Memory Management","ko":"ScaleSim: invocation distance 기반 메모리 관리로 대규모 multi-agent 시뮬레이션 제공","authors":"Zaifeng Pan, Yipeng Shen, Zhengding Hu, Zhuang Wang, Aninda Manocha, Zheng Wang, zhongkai yu, Yue Guan, Yufei Ding","pos":"#3708","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=kpJIOi10TX","abs":"LLM-based multi-agent simulations are increasingly adopted across application domains, but remain difficult to scale due to GPU memory pressure. Each agent maintains private GPU-resident states, including models, prefix caches, and adapters, which quickly exhaust device memory as the agent count grows. We identify two key properties of these workloads: sparse agent activation and an estimable agent invocation order. Based on an analysis of representative workload classes, we introduce invocation distance, a unified abstraction that estimates the relative order in which agents will issue future LLM requests. Leveraging this abstraction, we present ScaleSim, a memory-efficient LLM serving system for large-scale multi-agent simulations. ScaleSim enables proactive prefetching and priority-based eviction, supports diverse agent-specific memory through a modular interface, and achieves up to 1.74$\\times$ speedup over SGLang on simulation benchmarks.","absKo":"LLM-based multi-agent simulation은 다양한 응용 도메인에서 점점 더 많이 채택되고 있지만, GPU memory pressure 때문에 확장성이 떨어진다. 각 agent는 model, prefix cache, adapter를 포함한 private GPU-resident state를 유지하며, agent 수가 늘어날수록 device memory가 빠르게 소진된다. 우리는 이러한 workload의 두 가지 핵심 속성, 즉 sparse agent activation과 추정 가능한 agent invocation order를 식별한다. 대표적인 workload class에 대한 분석을 바탕으로, 우리는 agent가 미래에 LLM request를 발행할 상대적 순서를 추정하는 통합 abstraction인 invocation distance를 도입한다. 이 abstraction을 활용하여, 대규모 multi-agent simulation을 위한 memory-efficient LLM serving system인 ScaleSim을 제안한다. ScaleSim은 proactive prefetching과 priority-based eviction을 가능하게 하며, modular interface를 통해 다양한 agent-specific memory를 지원하고, simulation benchmark에서 SGLang 대비 최대 1.74$\\times$의 속도 향상을 달성한다."},{"id":"65166","en":"Row-stochastic matrices can provably outperform doubly stochastic matrices in decentralized learning","ko":"분산 학습에서 행-확률 행렬이 이중 확률 행렬을 입증 가능하게 능가할 수 있다","authors":"Bing Liu, Boao Kong, Limin Lu, Kun Yuan, Chengcheng Zhao","pos":"#3709","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=GAQE4Wr53f","abs":"Decentralized learning often involves a weighted global loss with heterogeneous node weights $\\lambda$. We revisit two natural strategies for incorporating these weights: (i) embedding them into the local losses to retain a uniform weight (and thus a doubly stochastic matrix), and (ii) keeping the original losses while employing a $\\lambda$-induced row-stochastic matrix. Although prior work shows that both strategies yield the same expected descent direction for the global loss, it remains unclear whether the Euclidean-space guarantees are tight and what fundamentally differentiates their behaviors. To clarify this, we develop a weighted Hilbert-space framework $L^2(\\lambda;\\mathbb{R}^d)$ and obtain convergence rates that are strictly tighter than those from Euclidean analysis. In this geometry, the row-stochastic matrix becomes self-adjoint whereas the doubly stochastic one does not, creating additional penalty terms that amplify consensus error, thereby slowing convergence. Consequently, the difference in convergence arises not only from spectral gaps but also from these penalty terms. We then derive sufficient conditions under which the row-stochastic design converges faster even with a smaller spectral gap. Finally, by using a Rayleigh-quotient and Loewner-order eigenvalue comparison, we further obtain topology conditions that guarantee this advantage and yield practical topology-design guidelines."},{"id":"61991","en":"Robust Federated Learning Against Adaptive Compression","ko":"adaptive compression에 대한 robust federated learning","authors":"Wenjing Yan, Xiangyu Zhong, Angela Yingjun Zhang","pos":"#3710","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=kvTL1G2kHG","abs":"<p>This paper addresses the critical challenges of hyperparameter tuning and communication efficiency in federated learning (FL). Despite recent advancements in parameter-free FL algorithms such as PAdaMFed, significant communication overhead remains a major obstacle to their practical deployment. To tackle these challenges, we propose a novel communication-efficient parameter-free FL algorithm ParFreFL that halves the communication requirements of PAdaMFed while preserving its parameter-free property. Building on this foundation, we introduce a compressed variant, ComParFreFL, which unifies the momentum increment and error feedback into a single parameter, effectively handling biased compression while maintaining the minimal communication cost. Notably, ComParFreFL also operates independent of the compression ratio, representing the first instance of such robustness in the compressed FL literature to our knowledge. Theoretically, our methods are proven to handle arbitrary data heterogeneity, partial client participation, and achieve linear speedup with respect to both local updates and participating clients. Extensive empirical evaluations demonstrate that our approaches match or slightly surpass the performance of carefully tuned alternatives while significantly reducing communication overhead, making FL more accessible and deployable in dynamic, resource-constrained environments.</p>","absKo":"<p>이 논문은 federated learning(FL)에서의 hyperparameter tuning과 communication efficiency라는 핵심 과제를 다룬다. PAdaMFed와 같은 parameter-free FL algorithm의 최근 발전에도 불구하고, 상당한 communication overhead는 여전히 실용적 배포의 주요 장애물로 남아 있다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 PAdaMFed의 parameter-free 특성을 유지하면서 communication 요구량을 절반으로 줄인 새로운 communication-efficient parameter-free FL algorithm인 ParFreFL을 제안한다. 이 기반 위에서, 우리는 momentum increment와 error feedback을 하나의 parameter로 통합하여 biased compression을 효과적으로 처리하면서도 최소 communication cost를 유지하는 compressed variant ComParFreFL을 소개한다. 주목할 점은, ComParFreFL이 compression ratio와 무관하게 동작하며, 우리가 아는 한 compressed FL 문헌에서 이러한 robustness의 첫 사례라는 것이다. 이론적으로 우리의 방법은 arbitrary data heterogeneity, partial client participation을 처리하고, local updates와 participating clients 양쪽에 대해 linear speedup을 달성함이 증명된다. 광범위한 실증 평가에서는 우리의 접근이 면밀히 튜닝된 대안들과 성능이 같거나 약간 더 우수하면서도 communication overhead를 크게 줄여, FL을 dynamic하고 resource-constrained한 환경에서 더 쉽게 접근 가능하고 배포 가능하게 만든다는 점을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"60616","en":"On the Role of Batch Size in Stochastic Conditional Gradient Methods","ko":"확률적 조건부 그래디언트 방법에서 배치 크기의 역할","authors":"Rustem Islamov, Roman Machacek, Aurelien Lucchi, Antonio Silveti-Falls, Eduard Gorbunov, Volkan Cevher","pos":"#3711","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=yTFTLj7MoN","abs":"We study the role of batch size in stochastic conditional gradient methods under a $\\mu$-Kurdyka–Łojasiewicz ($\\mu$-KL) condition. Focusing on momentum-based stochastic Frank–Wolfe–type conditional gradient algorithms (e.g., Scion), we derive a new analysis that explicitly captures the interaction between stepsize, batch size, and stochastic noise. Our study reveals a regime-dependent behavior: increasing the batch size initially improves optimization accuracy, but beyond a critical threshold, the benefits saturate and can eventually degrade performance under a fixed token budget. Notably, the theory predicts the magnitude of the optimal stepsize and aligns well with empirical practices observed in large-scale training. Leveraging these insights, we derive principled guidelines for selecting the batch size and stepsize, and propose an adaptive strategy that increases batch size and sequence length during training while preserving convergence guarantees. Preliminary experiments are consistent with the theoretical predictions and illustrate the emergence of the predicted scaling regimes. Overall, our results provide a theoretical framework for understanding batch-size scaling in stochastic conditional gradient methods and offer guidance for designing efficient training schedules in large-scale optimization.","absKo":"우리는 $\\mu$-Kurdyka–Łojasiewicz ($\\mu$-KL) 조건 하에서 stochastic conditional gradient 방법에서 batch size의 역할을 연구한다. momentum 기반 stochastic Frank–Wolfe 계열 conditional gradient algorithm(예: Scion)에 초점을 맞춰, stepsize, batch size, stochastic noise의 상호작용을 명시적으로 포착하는 새로운 분석을 도출한다. 우리의 연구는 regime-dependent behavior를 보여준다. batch size를 늘리면 처음에는 optimization accuracy가 향상되지만, 임계값을 넘어서면 그 이득이 포화되고 결국 고정된 token budget 아래에서는 성능이 저하될 수 있다. 특히 이 이론은 optimal stepsize의 크기를 예측하며, 대규모 학습에서 관찰되는 실무적 관행과도 잘 부합한다. 이러한 통찰을 활용하여 우리는 batch size와 stepsize 선택에 대한 원칙적인 지침을 도출하고, convergence guarantee를 유지하면서 학습 중 batch size와 sequence length를 증가시키는 adaptive strategy를 제안한다. 예비 실험은 이론적 예측과 일치하며, 예측된 scaling regime의 출현을 보여준다. 전반적으로 우리의 결과는 stochastic conditional gradient method에서 batch-size scaling을 이해하기 위한 이론적 틀을 제공하고, 대규모 optimization을 위한 효율적인 training schedule 설계에 대한 지침을 제시한다."},{"id":"64482","en":"OServe: Accelerating LLM Serving via Spatial-Temporal Workload Orchestration","ko":"OServe: 시공간 워크로드 오케스트레이션을 통한 LLM 서빙 가속","authors":"Youhe Jiang, Fangcheng Fu, Taiyi Wang, Guoliang He, Eiko Yoneki","pos":"#3712","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=N8JsmN0nQE","abs":"Serving Large Language Models (LLMs) can benefit immensely from parallelizing both the model and input requests across multiple devices, but incoming workloads exhibit substantial spatial and temporal heterogeneity. Spatially, workloads comprise heterogeneous requests with varying compute and memory demands. Temporally, workload composition varies over time. Nevertheless, existing systems typically assume spatially uniform and temporally stable workloads, employing a homogeneous, static model deployment. This mismatch between the assumption and real-world spatial-temporal heterogeneity results in suboptimal performance. We present OServe, an LLM serving system with heterogeneous and flexible model deployment that addresses both spatial and temporal heterogeneity. First, OServe introduces a novel workload-aware scheduling algorithm that optimizes heterogeneous model deployments according to real-time workload characteristics. Second, OServe proposes an efficient workload-adaptive switching method that migrates model deployments in response to predicted workload changes. Experiments on real-world traces show that OServe improves performance by up to 2$\\times$ (average: 1.5$\\times$) compared to state-of-the-art serving systems.","absKo":"대형 언어 모델(LLMs) 서빙은 여러 디바이스에 걸쳐 모델과 입력 요청을 병렬화함으로써 큰 이점을 얻을 수 있지만, 유입되는 workload는 상당한 공간적 및 시간적 이질성을 보인다. 공간적으로는 workload가 서로 다른 compute 및 memory 요구량을 가진 이질적인 요청들로 구성된다. 시간적으로는 workload의 구성비가 시간에 따라 변한다. 그럼에도 불구하고 기존 시스템은 대체로 공간적으로 균일하고 시간적으로 안정적인 workload를 가정하며, 균질하고 정적인 model deployment를 사용한다. 이러한 가정과 실제 공간-시간적 이질성의 불일치는 비최적의 성능으로 이어진다. 우리는 공간적 및 시간적 이질성을 모두 다루는, 이질적이고 유연한 model deployment를 갖춘 LLM serving system인 OServe를 제안한다. 첫째, OServe는 실시간 workload 특성에 따라 이질적 model deployment를 최적화하는 새로운 workload-aware scheduling 알고리즘을 도입한다. 둘째, OServe는 예측된 workload 변화에 대응하여 model deployment를 이동시키는 효율적인 workload-adaptive switching 방법을 제안한다. 실제 trace에 대한 실험은 OServe가 최첨단 serving system과 비교해 성능을 최대 2$\\times$(평균: 1.5$\\times$) 향상시킴을 보여준다."},{"id":"66517","en":"Mitigating Staleness in Asynchronous Pipeline Parallelism via Basis Rotation","ko":"기저 회전을 통한 비동기 파이프라인 병렬성에서의 지연 완화","authors":"Hyunji Jung, Sungbin Shin, Namhoon Lee","pos":"#3713","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=31iky6wFu5","abs":"<p>Asynchronous pipeline parallelism maximizes hardware utilization by eliminating the pipeline bubbles inherent in synchronous execution, offering a path toward efficient large-scale distributed training. However, this efficiency gain can be compromised by gradient staleness, where the immediate model updates with delayed gradients introduce noise into the optimization process. Crucially, we identify a critical, yet often overlooked, pathology: this delay scales linearly with pipeline depth, fundamentally undermining the very scalability that the method originally intends to provide. In this work, we investigate this inconsistency and bridge the gap by rectifying delayed gradients through basis rotation, restoring scalable asynchronous training while maintaining performance. Specifically, we observe that the deleterious effects of delayed gradients are exacerbated when the Hessian eigenbasis is misaligned with the standard coordinate basis. We demonstrate that this misalignment prevents coordinate-wise adaptive schemes, such as Adam, from effectively leveraging curvature-aware adaptivity. This failure leads to significant oscillations in the optimization trajectory and, consequently, slower convergence. We substantiate these findings through both rigorous theoretical analysis and empirical evaluation. To address this challenge, we propose the use of basis rotation, demonstrating that it effectively mitigates the alignment issue and significantly accelerates convergence in asynchronous settings. For example, our training of a 1B-parameter LLM with basis rotation achieves the same training loss in 76.8% fewer iterations compared to the best-performing asynchronous pipeline parallel training baseline.</p>"},{"id":"65135","en":"Matrix-Free GPU Semidefinite Programming for Quantum Ordered Search at the k=6 Frontier","ko":"행렬 없는 GPU 반정부호 계획법을 통한 k=6 최전선의 양자 순서 탐색","authors":"Yancheng Wu, Huikang Liu, Wenzhi Gao, Yuexin Su, Tongyang Li, Dongdong Ge, Yinyu Ye","pos":"#3714","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=GSGOyxRrBo","abs":"Quantum computation offers the potential for a significant constant-factor speedup for the Ordered Search Problem (OSP). A classical construction is the $k$-query quantum ordered search algorithm, which can exactly search an $N$-element ordered list and achieves a query complexity improvement of a factor of $\\frac{k}{\\log_2 N}$. For larger $k$,  stronger constant-factor improvements could be obtained by finding the largest admissible list size $N^\\star$, a task that can be formulated as a structured semidefinite program (SDP). However, solving this SDP becomes computationally intractable beyond $k=6$, as existing CPU and GPU solvers rely on explicit construction of prohibitively large constraint matrices. In this paper, we introduce a matrix-free GPU SDP framework that evaluates the highly structured constraints in OSP on-the-fly using custom CUDA kernels, reducing memory complexity from quadratic to linear and shifting the bottleneck from memory to computation. Using this approach, we tightly bracket the optimal list size for $k=6$ as $90,000 \\le N^\\star &lt; 94,000$, improving the best known upper bound on the query coefficient from $0.390$ to $0.365$. We further certify these results by constructing rigorous dual infeasibility certificates via matrix-free minimum-eigenvalue estimation."},{"id":"63703","en":"Improved Analysis of the Accelerated Noisy Power Method with Applications to Decentralized PCA","ko":"Decentralized PCA에의 응용을 포함한 Accelerated Noisy Power Method의 개선된 분석","authors":"Pierre Aguié, Mathieu Even, Laurent Massoulié","pos":"#3715","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=UTiEfkfNQ2","abs":"<p>We analyze the Accelerated Noisy Power Method, an algorithm for Principal Component Analysis in the setting where only inexact matrix-vector products are available, which can arise for instance in decentralized PCA. While previous works have established that acceleration can improve convergence rates compared to the standard Noisy Power Method, these guarantees require overly restrictive upper bounds on the magnitude of the perturbations, limiting their practical applicability. We provide an improved analysis of this algorithm, which preserves the accelerated convergence rate under much milder conditions on the perturbations. We show that our new analysis is worst-case optimal, in the sense that the convergence rate cannot be improved, and that the noise conditions we derive cannot be relaxed without sacrificing convergence guarantees. We demonstrate the practical relevance of our results by deriving an accelerated algorithm for decentralized PCA, which has similar communication costs to non-accelerated methods. To our knowledge, this is the first decentralized algorithm for PCA with provably accelerated convergence.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 Accelerated Noisy Power Method를 분석한다. 이 알고리즘은 부정확한 matrix-vector product만 उपलब्ध한 상황에서 Principal Component Analysis를 수행하는 방법으로, 예를 들어 decentralized PCA에서 나타날 수 있다. 이전 연구들은 acceleration이 standard Noisy Power Method에 비해 convergence rate를 개선할 수 있음을 보였지만, 이러한 보장은 perturbation 크기에 대해 지나치게 제한적인 상한을 요구하여 실제 적용 가능성을 제한했다. 우리는 perturbation에 대한 훨씬 완화된 조건하에서도 accelerated convergence rate를 유지하는 이 알고리즘의 개선된 분석을 제시한다. 우리의 새로운 분석이 worst-case optimal임을 보이며, convergence rate는 더 개선될 수 없고, 우리가 유도한 noise condition도 convergence guarantee를 희생하지 않고는 완화될 수 없음을 보인다. 또한 decentralized PCA를 위한 accelerated algorithm을 유도하여 결과의 실용적 관련성을 입증하는데, 이 알고리즘은 non-accelerated method와 유사한 communication cost를 가진다. 우리가 아는 한, 이는 provably accelerated convergence를 갖는 첫 번째 decentralized PCA 알고리즘이다.</p>"},{"id":"62713","en":"A Tight Theory of Error Feedback Algorithms in Distributed Optimization","ko":"분산 최적화에서 Error Feedback 알고리즘의 Tight Theory","authors":"Daniel Berg Thomsen, Adrien Taylor, Aymeric Dieuleveut","pos":"#3803","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=dyRD6lBH8K","abs":"<p>Communication costs are a major bottleneck in distributed learning and first-order optimization. A common approach to alleviate this issue is to compress the gradient information exchanged between agents. However, such compression typically degrades the convergence guarantees of gradient-based methods. Error feedback mechanisms provide a simple and computationally cheap remedy for this issue, but numerous variants have been proposed, and their relative performance remains poorly understood. In this work, we provide tight convergence analyses for two of the main error feedback algorithms in the literature, namely error feedback and EF21. Our results hold independently of the number of participating agents and rely on the construction of novel Lyapunov functions that recover the known best guarantees in the single-agent regime.</p>","absKo":"<p>Communication cost는 distributed learning과 first-order optimization에서 주요 병목이다. 이 문제를 완화하는 일반적인 접근법은 agent 간에 교환되는 gradient information을 압축하는 것이다. 그러나 이러한 compression은 일반적으로 gradient-based method의 convergence guarantee를 저하시킨다. Error feedback mechanism은 이 문제에 대한 간단하고 계산 비용이 낮은 해결책을 제공하지만, 수많은 variant가 제안되었고 그 상대적 성능은 여전히 충분히 이해되지 않았다. 본 연구에서는 문헌에서 중요한 두 가지 error feedback algorithm, 즉 error feedback와 EF21에 대해 tight convergence analysis를 제시한다. 우리의 결과는 참여하는 agent 수와 무관하게 성립하며, single-agent regime에서 알려진 최선의 guarantee를 복원하는 새로운 Lyapunov function의 구성을 바탕으로 한다.</p>"},{"id":"66767","en":"Bottleneck Communication Delay Minimization for Communication-Efficient Decentralized Learning","ko":"통신 효율적 분산 학습을 위한 Bottleneck 통신 지연 최소화","authors":"Nozomi Hata, Kenta Niwa","pos":"#3804","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=0T8UmNuZJn","abs":"<p>For communication-efficient decentralized learning, advanced network (NW) topologies, such as exponential and 1-peer exponential graphs, have been studied under homogeneous communication delays. However, real-world NWs exhibit heterogeneous communication delays, making node assignment optimization crucial for minimizing the Bottleneck Communication Delay (BCD). We propose BTSP-MSR, an approximate method for minimizing BCD on circulant digraphs, including exponential and 1-peer exponential graphs. Leveraging the fact that circulant digraphs can be viewed as a union of (directed) ring graphs, we derive an upper bound on the BCD by combining the ring-graph BCD (BTSP) with a deviation term (MSR). We then construct a solver that sequentially minimizes these two terms. Numerical experiments show that BTSP-MSR consistently reduces BCD across several circulant digraphs with large numbers of nodes. Notably, incorporating the exponential or 1-peer exponential graph enables communication-efficient decentralized learning under heterogeneous delay settings.</p>"},{"id":"62179","en":"Breaking the Capacity Bottleneck in Model-Heterogeneous Federated Learning via Gradual Model Restoration","ko":"Gradual Model Restoration을 통한 모델 이기종 연합학습의 용량 병목 완화","authors":"Chengjie Ma, Seungeun Oh, Jihong Park, Seong-Lyun Kim","pos":"#3805","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=iziZOSvtGK","abs":"<p>Federated learning (FL) enables distributed model training, yet in heterogeneous deployments, Bandwidth-Constrained Clients (BCCs) often contribute inefficiently due to limited uplink bandwidth. In model-heterogeneous FL with fixed small sub-models, BCCs with sub-models may improve quickly in early rounds but become under-parameterized later, resulting in slow convergence and poor generalization. To address this challenge, we propose FedGMR, a federated learning framework centered around Gradual Model Restoration (GMR), where GMR progressively increases each client’s sub-model density during training, allowing BCCs to remain effective contributors throughout optimization. To make GMR practical under real-world heterogeneity, FedGMR is realized as an end-to-end workflow with asynchronous coordination and stable, mask-aware aggregation. We further establish convergence guarantees, showing that the aggregation error scales with the average sub-model density across clients and rounds, and that GMR provably narrows the gap toward full-model FL. Extensive experiments on FEMNIST, CIFAR-10, ImageNet-100, and StackOverflow demonstrate that FedGMR improves both convergence speed and final accuracy, especially under severe heterogeneity and non-IID data distributions.</p>","absKo":"<p>Federated learning(FL)은 분산 model training을 가능하게 하지만, heterogeneous deployment에서는 Bandwidth-Constrained Clients(BCCs)가 제한된 uplink bandwidth 때문에 비효율적으로 기여하는 경우가 많다. 고정된 작은 sub-model을 사용하는 model-heterogeneous FL에서 sub-model을 가진 BCC는 초기 round에서는 빠르게 개선될 수 있지만, 이후에는 under-parameterized 상태가 되어 수렴이 느려지고 generalization이 저하된다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 Gradual Model Restoration(GMR)을 중심으로 한 federated learning framework인 FedGMR을 제안한다. GMR은 학습 중 각 client의 sub-model density를 점진적으로 증가시켜, BCC가 optimization 전반에 걸쳐 효과적인 기여를 유지하도록 한다. 현실적인 heterogeneity 하에서 GMR을 실용적으로 만들기 위해, FedGMR은 asynchronous coordination과 stable, mask-aware aggregation을 갖춘 end-to-end workflow로 구현된다. 우리는 또한 수렴 보장을 확립하여, aggregation error가 client와 round 전반의 평균 sub-model density에 따라 스케일되며, GMR이 full-model FL과의 격차를 이론적으로 좁힌다는 점을 보인다. FEMNIST, CIFAR-10, ImageNet-100, StackOverflow에서의 광범위한 실험은 FedGMR이 특히 심한 heterogeneity와 non-IID data distribution 하에서 수렴 속도와 최종 정확도를 모두 향상시킴을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"65724","en":"Clipping Makes Distributed and Federated Asynchronous SGD Robust to Stragglers","ko":"클리핑은 분산·연합 비동기 SGD를 낙오자에 강건하게 만든다","authors":"Samuel Erickson, Mikael Johansson","pos":"#3806","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=AmgjQp4vrr","abs":"<p>In modern machine learning, parallelization of training is an important strategy for increasing scale. Asynchronous stochastic gradient descent (ASGD), which maximally utilizes available hardware, avoids having to wait for slow workers. However, with constant step sizes, the convergence of ASGD is nonetheless negatively effected by slow workers due to large delays in updates. At the same time, it has been empirically observed in asynchronous training of deep learning models that gradient clipping ``stabilizes'' training. In this work, we provide a theoretical justification for this behavior, as we show that clipping removes the dependence of the maximum delay in the oracle complexity. We employ a sub-Weibull model of gradient noise which generalize sub-Gaussian and sub-exponential disitributions to more heavy-tailed distributions, motivated by empirical observations in deep learning. We show convergence in expectation, and for the first time in asynchronous optimization, convergence with high probability.</p>"},{"id":"63064","en":"DistFlow: A Fully Distributed RL Framework for Scalable and Efficient LLM Post-Training","ko":"DistFlow: 확장 가능하고 효율적인 LLM 사후 학습을 위한 완전 분산 RL 프레임워크","authors":"zhixin wang, Jiaming Xu, Tianyi Zhou, Mingjun Zhang, Liming Liu, JiaruiHu, Dian Yang, TongYu Wang, Ping Zhang, Jinlong Hou, Siyuan Feng, Yuan Cheng, Yuan Qi","pos":"#3809","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=aPPEyZpKkp","abs":"<p>Effectively scaling Reinforcement Learning (RL) is crucial for enhancing the reasoning and alignment of Large Language Models. The massive data and complex execution flows inherent in these tasks require a distributed architecture capable of efficient scaling. However, to simplify programming and dependency management, mainstream frameworks often rely on a centralized architecture where a single node dispatches both control and data. This inherent coupling creates significant communication bottlenecks, severely limiting system scalability and efficiency. We present DistFlow, a novel, fully distributed RL framework that adopts a multi-controller paradigm. By decoupling data transmission from control dispatch, DistFlow establishes a parallelism-aware, decentralized Data Coordinator that leverages local caching, load balancing, and asynchronous double buffer to minimize communication overhead and mitigate straggler effects. For control logic, it introduces a task scheduler built upon Directed Acyclic Graph (DAG) that facilitates fine-grained, independent execution. Experimental results demonstrate that DistFlow achieves near-linear scalability up to 512 GPUs and delivers up to a 2.63x throughput improvement over state-of-the-art (SOTA) frameworks.</p>","absKo":"<p>Reinforcement Learning (RL)을 효과적으로 scale하는 것은 Large Language Models의 reasoning과 alignment를 향상시키는 데 매우 중요하다. 이러한 task에 내재된 방대한 데이터와 복잡한 execution flow는 효율적으로 확장 가능한 distributed architecture를 필요로 한다. 그러나 programming과 dependency management를 단순화하기 위해, 주류 framework는 종종 하나의 node가 control과 data를 모두 dispatch하는 centralized architecture에 의존한다. 이러한 본질적 결합은 심각한 communication bottleneck을 만들어 시스템의 scalability와 efficiency를 크게 제한한다. 우리는 multi-controller paradigm을 채택한 새롭고 완전한 distributed RL framework인 DistFlow를 제시한다. data transmission과 control dispatch를 분리함으로써, DistFlow는 local caching, load balancing, asynchronous double buffer를 활용해 communication overhead를 최소화하고 straggler effect를 완화하는 parallelism-aware decentralized Data Coordinator를 구축한다. control logic 측면에서는 fine-grained하고 독립적인 execution을 지원하는 Directed Acyclic Graph (DAG) 기반 task scheduler를 도입한다. 실험 결과는 DistFlow가 최대 512 GPUs까지 거의 선형에 가까운 scalability를 달성하고, state-of-the-art (SOTA) framework 대비 최대 2.63배의 throughput 향상을 제공함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"62830","en":"FAB: A First-Order AB-based Gradient Algorithm for Distributed Bilevel Optimization over Time-Varying Directed Graphs","ko":"FAB: 시간 변화 유향 그래프에서 분산 Bilevel Optimization을 위한 1차 AB 기반 Gradient 알고리즘","authors":"Yaoshuai Ma, Xiao Wang, Wei Yao, Jin Zhang","pos":"#3810","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=coINrhVRkL","abs":"<p>Distributed optimization over time-varying directed graphs has shown promising performance in addressing challenges posed by complex communication constraints in real-world scenarios.  In many practical settings, however, the direct application of distributed optimization algorithms encounters additional difficulties, most notably hyperparameter tuning, which our empirical observations suggest can be effectively mitigated by integrating bilevel optimization.  Motivated by these findings, we study distributed bilevel optimization over time-varying directed networks, a problem that remains largely unexplored due to the compounded challenges arising from consensus bias in dynamic unbalanced communication and the nested optimization structure.  In this work, we propose a fully first-order distributed gradient-based algorithm that integrates the Push–Pull (also known as AB) communication strategy with a value function-based penalty method and establish its non-asymptotic convergence properties.  Notably, a simplified variant of our analysis framework for nonconvex single-level distributed optimization establishes a convergence rate for the Push–Pull algorithm, thereby resolving an open question concerning its convergence over time-varying directed graphs.   Empirical evaluations across diverse tasks, including hyperparameter tuning, data hyper-cleaning, and reinforcement learning, validate the effectiveness and efficiency of the proposed algorithm.</p>","absKo":"<p>시간에 따라 변하는 directed graph 위의 distributed optimization은 현실 세계의 복잡한 communication constraint가 초래하는 문제를 해결하는 데 유망한 성능을 보여주었다. 그러나 많은 실용적 설정에서 distributed optimization algorithm을 직접 적용하면 추가적인 어려움, 특히 hyperparameter tuning 문제가 발생하며, 우리의 empirical observation은 bilevel optimization을 통합함으로써 이를 효과적으로 완화할 수 있음을 시사한다. 이러한 발견에 동기부여를 받아, 우리는 dynamic unbalanced communication에서의 consensus bias와 nested optimization structure가 복합적으로 만들어내는 어려움 때문에 아직 충분히 탐구되지 않은 문제인 time-varying directed network 위의 distributed bilevel optimization을 연구한다. 본 연구에서는 Push–Pull(AB라고도 함) communication strategy를 value function-based penalty method와 결합한 완전한 first-order distributed gradient-based algorithm을 제안하고, 그 non-asymptotic convergence property를 확립한다. 특히, nonconvex single-level distributed optimization에 대한 우리의 analysis framework를 단순화한 variant는 Push–Pull algorithm에 대한 convergence rate를 확립하여, time-varying directed graph에서의 convergence에 관한 열린 질문을 해결한다. hyperparameter tuning, data hyper-cleaning, reinforcement learning을 포함한 다양한 task에 대한 empirical evaluation은 제안한 algorithm의 효과성과 효율성을 검증한다.</p>"},{"id":"66683","en":"Factored Gossip DiLoCo: Reducing Blocking Communication within DiLoCo","ko":"Factored Gossip DiLoCo: DiLoCo 내 Blocking 통신 감소","authors":"Chamin Hewa Koneputugodage, Thalaiyasingam Ajanthan, Sameera Ramasinghe, Hadi Mohaghegh Dolatabadi, Shamane Siriwardhana, Gil Avraham, Violetta Shevchenko, Karol Pajak, James Snewin, Alexander Long","pos":"#3811","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=1MynM9hkFH","abs":"<p>To make large-scale distributed training practical outside high-bandwidth datacenters, we must reduce blocking, high-volume synchronization. While DiLoCo communicates infrequently, its outer synchronization remains bandwidth-heavy and brittle to stragglers and transient failures. We relax exact synchronization to approximate synchronization via mixing/gossip, which degrades gracefully under delays and communication failures. This allows us to factorize DiLoCo synchronization into a non-blocking mixing step that overlaps computation with no staleness, and a blocking mixing step that tightens worker agreement, yielding a tunable trade-off between compute utilization and optimization stability. On up to billion-parameter language models in low-bandwidth settings, our method substantially improves compute utilization while matching DiLoCo’s training progress, and is more robust to failures.</p>"},{"id":"62078","en":"FedCDWA: Decoupled Federated Prototype Distillation with Hierarchical Wasserstein Aggregation","ko":"FedCDWA: 계층적 Wasserstein 집계를 통한 분리형 연합 프로토타입 증류","authors":"Zhenshen Liu, Kai Fan, Wenjie Li, Kuan Zhang, HUI LI, Yintang Yang","pos":"#3812","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=k0qTjaVatI","abs":"<p>Federated learning enables decentralized clients to collaboratively train models without sharing local data. However, heterogeneous client distributions often induce client drift and hinder convergence. This paper proposes FedCDWA, a decoupled hierarchical federated distillation framework. FedCDWA decouples client-side personalized distillation from server-side mutual distillation to mitigate distillation-induced optimization conflicts. It further adopts Hierarchical Wasserstein Aggregation to aggregate prototypes without restrictive parametric assumptions while preserving intra-class structure and inter-class geometry. To achieve finer-grained feature alignment, Prototype–Variance Dual Alignment matches feature means and variances in the feature space. We prove convergence guarantees for FedCDWA. Experiments on three datasets demonstrate that FedCDWA consistently improves both global and personalized accuracy across heterogeneity levels, with smaller performance degradation under more severe heterogeneity.</p>","absKo":"Federated learning은 decentralized client들이 로컬 데이터를 공유하지 않고도 함께 model을 학습할 수 있게 한다. 그러나 heterogeneous client distribution은 종종 client drift를 유발하고 수렴을 저해한다. 본 논문은 decoupled hierarchical federated distillation framework인 FedCDWA를 제안한다. FedCDWA는 distillation으로 인한 optimization conflict를 완화하기 위해 client-side personalized distillation과 server-side mutual distillation을 분리한다. 또한 제한적인 parametric assumption 없이 prototype을 집계하면서도 class 내 구조와 class 간 기하를 보존하기 위해 Hierarchical Wasserstein Aggregation을 채택한다. 더 정밀한 feature alignment를 달성하기 위해 Prototype–Variance Dual Alignment는 feature space에서 feature mean과 variance를 맞춘다. 우리는 FedCDWA에 대한 수렴 보장을 증명한다. 세 개의 dataset에서 수행한 실험은 FedCDWA가 heterogeneity 수준 전반에서 global accuracy와 personalized accuracy를 모두 일관되게 향상시키며, 더 심한 heterogeneity에서도 성능 저하가 더 작음을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"64374","en":"FedQueue: Queue-Aware Federated Learning for Cross-Facility HPC Training","ko":"FedQueue: 시설 간 HPC 학습을 위한 큐 인식 연합 학습","authors":"Yijiang Li, Emon Dey, Zilinghan Li, Krishnan Raghavan, Ravi Madduri, Kibaek Kim","pos":"#3813","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ODWi7lbMGU","abs":"Federated learning~(FL) across multiple HPC facilities faces stochastic \\emph{admission delays} from batch schedulers that dominate wall-clock time. Synchronous FL suffers from severe stragglers, while asynchronous FL accumulates stale updates when queues spike. We propose \\fedqueue{}, a queue-aware FL protocol that incorporates scheduler delays directly into training and aggregation, which (i) predicts per-facility queue delays online to budget local work, (ii) applies cutoff-based admission that buffers late arrivals to bound staleness, and (iii) performs staleness-aware aggregation to stabilize heterogeneous local workloads. We prove the convergence for non-convex objectives at rate $\\mathcal{O}(1/\\sqrt{R})$ under bounded staleness, and show that the admission controls yield bounded staleness with high probability under queue-prediction error. Real-world cross-facility deployment of \\fedqueue{} shows 20.5\\% improvement over baseline algorithms. Controlled queue simulations demonstrate robust improvement over the baselines; in particular, about 34\\% reduction in time to reach a target accuracy level under high queue variance and non-IID partitions.","absKo":"여러 HPC facility에 걸친 Federated learning~(FL)은 batch scheduler로부터 발생하는 stochastic \\emph{admission delays} 때문에 wall-clock time의 대부분을 소모한다. Synchronous FL은 심각한 straggler 문제를 겪는 반면, asynchronous FL은 queue가 급증할 때 stale update를 누적한다. 우리는 scheduler 지연을 training과 aggregation에 직접 반영하는 queue-aware FL protocol인 \\fedqueue{}를 제안한다. 이 protocol은 (i) facility별 queue delay를 online으로 예측하여 local work를 배분하고, (ii) cutoff-based admission을 적용해 늦게 도착한 작업을 buffer하여 staleness를 제한하며, (iii) staleness-aware aggregation을 수행해 이질적인 local workload를 안정화한다. 우리는 bounded staleness 하에서 비볼록 목적함수에 대해 $\\mathcal{O}(1/\\sqrt{R})$의 수렴을 증명하며, admission control이 queue prediction error가 있을 때에도 높은 확률로 bounded staleness를 보장함을 보인다. 실제 cross-facility 배포에서 \\fedqueue{}는 baseline algorithm 대비 20.5\\%의 성능 향상을 보인다. 통제된 queue simulation은 baseline에 대한 견고한 개선을 보여주며, 특히 높은 queue variance와 non-IID partition 하에서 목표 accuracy 수준에 도달하는 시간을 약 34\\% 줄인다."},{"id":"65376","en":"HO-SFL: Hybrid-Order Split Federated Learning with Backprop-Free Clients and Dimension-Free Aggregation","ko":"HO-SFL: Backprop 없는 클라이언트와 차원 없는 집계를 갖춘 Hybrid-Order Split Federated Learning","authors":"Qiyuan Chen, Xian Wu, Yi Wang, Xianhao Chen","pos":"#3814","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=EETUbVsG6X","abs":"<p>Fine-tuning large models on edge devices is severely hindered by the memory-intensive backpropagation (BP) in standard frameworks like federated learning and split learning. While substituting BP with zeroth-order optimization can significantly reduce memory footprints, it typically suffers from prohibitively degraded convergence speed. To resolve this dilemma, we propose <em>Hybrid-Order Split Federated Learning</em> (HO-SFL). By reformulating the split learning process within a Lagrangian framework, HO-SFL decouples the optimization landscape: The server performs precise first-order updates (i.e., BP), whereas clients conduct memory-efficient zeroth-order optimization. This hybrid design not only eliminates the need for client-side BP but also enables dimension-free model aggregation, drastically lowering communication costs. Crucially, we provide a theoretical convergence analysis, demonstrating that HO-SFL mitigates the dimension-dependent convergence slowdown of zeroth-order optimization, achieving a convergence rate comparable to first-order methods. Extensive experiments on tasks across vision and language modalities validate that HO-SFL achieves convergence speeds comparable to first-order baselines while significantly reducing communication costs and client memory footprints.</p>"},{"id":"60696","en":"High-Probability Convergence Guarantees of Decentralized SGD","ko":"Decentralized SGD의 High-Probability Convergence 보장","authors":"Aleksandar Armacki, Ali Sayed","pos":"#3815","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=xSYhEkiyp5","abs":"Convergence in high-probability (HP) has attracted increasing interest, due to implying exponentially decaying tail bounds and strong guarantees for individual runs of an algorithm. While many works study HP guarantees in centralized settings, much less is understood in the decentralized setup, where existing works require strong assumptions, like uniformly bounded gradients, or asymptotically vanishing noise. This results in a significant gap between the assumptions used to establish convergence in the HP and the mean-squared error (MSE) sense, and is also contrary to centralized settings, where it is known that $\\mathtt{SGD}$ converges in HP under the same conditions on the cost function as needed for MSE convergence. Motivated by these observations, we study the HP convergence of Decentralized $\\mathtt{SGD}$ ($\\mathtt{DSGD}$) in the presence of light-tailed noise, providing several strong results. First, we show that $\\mathtt{DSGD}$ converges in HP under the same conditions on the cost as in the MSE sense, removing the restrictive assumptions used in prior works. Second, our sharp analysis yields order-optimal rates for both non-convex and strongly convex costs. Third, we establish a linear speed-up in the number of users, leading to matching, or strictly better transient times than those obtained from MSE results, further underlining the tightness of our analysis. To the best of our knowledge, this is the first work that shows $\\mathtt{DSGD}$ achieves a linear speed-up in the HP sense. Our relaxed assumptions and sharp rates stem from several technical results of independent interest, including a result on the variance-reduction effect of decentralized methods in the HP sense, as well as a novel bound on the MGF of strongly convex costs, which is of interest even in centralized settings. Finally, we provide experiments that validate our theory.","absKo":"High-probability (HP)에서의 convergence는 exponentially decaying tail bounds와 알고리즘의 개별 실행에 대한 강한 보장을 함의하기 때문에 점점 더 큰 관심을 받고 있다. 많은 연구가 centralized settings에서의 HP 보장을 다루는 반면, decentralized setup에서는 훨씬 덜 이해되어 왔으며, 기존 연구들은 uniformly bounded gradients나 asymptotically vanishing noise처럼 강한 가정을 요구한다. 이로 인해 HP와 mean-squared error (MSE) 관점에서 convergence를 확립하기 위해 사용되는 가정 사이에 상당한 간극이 생기며, 이는 centralized settings와도 대조적이다. 중앙집중형 설정에서는 $\\mathtt{SGD}$가 MSE convergence에 필요한 cost function의 동일한 조건 하에서 HP로 수렴한다는 것이 알려져 있다. 이러한 관찰에 동기를 얻어, 우리는 light-tailed noise가 존재하는 상황에서 Decentralized $\\mathtt{SGD}$ ($\\mathtt{DSGD}$)의 HP convergence를 연구하며 몇 가지 강한 결과를 제시한다. 첫째, $\\mathtt{DSGD}$가 MSE 관점과 동일한 cost 조건 하에서 HP로 수렴함을 보이며, 기존 연구에서 사용된 제약적 가정을 제거한다. 둘째, 우리의 정밀한 분석은 non-convex 및 strongly convex cost 모두에 대해 order-optimal rate를 도출한다. 셋째, 사용자 수에 대한 linear speed-up을 확립하여, MSE 결과에서 얻어지는 transient time과 일치하거나 더 우수한 시간을 제공하며, 우리의 분석이 얼마나 타이트한지를 더욱 뒷받침한다. 우리가 아는 한, $\\mathtt{DSGD}$가 HP 관점에서 linear speed-up을 달성함을 보인 첫 번째 연구이다. 우리의 완화된 가정과 정밀한 rate는 HP 관점에서 decentralized method의 variance-reduction 효과에 대한 결과, 그리고 centralized settings에서도 의미 있는 strongly convex cost의 MGF에 대한 새로운 bound를 포함한 여러 기술적 결과에서 비롯된다. 마지막으로, 우리는 이론을 검증하는 실험을 제시한다."},{"id":"62628","en":"HybridFlow: Resource-Adaptive Subtask Routing for Efficient Edge-Cloud LLM Inference","ko":"HybridFlow: 효율적 Edge-Cloud LLM Inference를 위한 자원 적응형 Subtask Routing","authors":"Jiangwen Dong, Jiayu Li, Tianhang Zheng, Wanyu LIN","pos":"#3816","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=erxWUWJlt2","abs":"<p>Edge-cloud collaborative inference is crucial for LLM-powered edge devices, as on-device models often lack the required reasoning capability, while cloud-only inference can be costly and slow under strict latency and token/API budgets. However, existing edge-cloud collaboration methods typically route input tasks based on their estimated difficulty. These static, coarse heuristics overlook subtask dependencies, missing opportunities for parallel execution and budget-adaptive routing. To this end, we propose HybridFlow, a resource-adaptive edge-cloud inference framework that enables parallel execution of interdependent subtasks.  Specifically, we build a dependency-aware DAG for each input task, facilitating concurrent execution of subtasks once their dependencies are resolved, thereby reducing end-to-end latency.  Additionally, we propose a dynamic benefit–cost utility model, optimizing the trade-off between accuracy, token/API cost, and latency in real-time. This dynamic routing minimizes unnecessary cloud usage while preserving reasoning quality.  Across GPQA, MMLU-Pro, AIME24, and LiveBench-Reasoning, HybridFlow improves the cost-accuracy trade-off, reducing latency and cloud API usage while maintaining competitive accuracy.</p>","absKo":"<p>edge-cloud collaborative inference는 LLM 기반 edge device에서 매우 중요하다. on-device model은 필요한 reasoning capability가 부족한 경우가 많고, cloud-only inference는 엄격한 latency와 token/API budget 하에서 비용이 많이 들고 느릴 수 있기 때문이다. 그러나 기존의 edge-cloud 협업 방법은 보통 입력 task를 추정된 난이도에 따라 라우팅한다. 이러한 정적이고 거친 heuristic은 subtask 간 의존성을 간과하여, 병렬 실행의 기회와 budget-adaptive routing 가능성을 놓친다. 이를 위해 우리는 상호의존적인 subtask의 병렬 실행을 가능하게 하는 resource-adaptive edge-cloud inference framework인 HybridFlow를 제안한다. 구체적으로, 각 입력 task에 대해 dependency-aware DAG를 구성하여, 의존성이 해소되는 즉시 subtask를 동시에 실행할 수 있게 하므로 end-to-end latency를 줄인다. 또한 정확도, token/API 비용, latency 간의 trade-off를 실시간으로 최적화하는 dynamic benefit-cost utility model을 제안한다. 이 dynamic routing은 reasoning quality를 유지하면서 불필요한 cloud 사용을 최소화한다. GPQA, MMLU-Pro, AIME24, LiveBench-Reasoning 전반에서 HybridFlow는 cost-accuracy trade-off를 개선하여, 경쟁력 있는 정확도를 유지하면서 latency와 cloud API 사용량을 줄인다.</p>"},{"id":"63743","en":"PACE: Proactive Agent-Level Admission Control for Efficient Agentic Batch Inference","ko":"PACE: 효율적인 Agentic Batch Inference를 위한 선제적 Agent 수준 Admission Control","authors":"Qiaoling Chen, Ethan Li, Tian Tang, Peng Sun, Boyu Tian, Guoteng Wang, Shenggui Li, Zhenhua Han, Yonggang Wen, Tianwei Zhang","pos":"#3913","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=U7c6glPdDW","abs":"<p>Batch inference for agentic workloads stresses the GPU key–value (KV) cache in a sustained and cumulative manner, often causing severe throughput degradation well before memory capacity is exhausted. We identify this phenomenon as middle-phase thrashing, a previously under-characterized pathology in which cache efficiency collapses as long-lived agents accumulate state over time.  We argue that mitigating this pathology requires moving beyond reactive, request-level cache management to proactive, agent-level admission control. Drawing inspiration from congestion control in distributed systems, we view the KV cache as a shared resource whose efficient utilization depends on feedback-driven regulation. Based on this insight, we present PACE, a lightweight control layer that regulates agent admission to bound aggregate cache pressure while preserving execution continuity. PACE adapts a cache-aware control algorithm to dynamically adjust the number of active agents using runtime cache signals.  Across large models and real-world agent workloads, PACE prevents middle-phase thrashing and improves batch inference throughput by up to 4.09× on Qwen3-32B and 1.90× on DeepSeek-V3, while remaining compatible with existing LLM serving systems.</p>","absKo":"<p>Agentic workload를 위한 batch inference는 GPU key–value(KV) cache에 지속적이고 누적적인 부담을 주며, 종종 메모리 용량이 다 소진되기도 전에 심각한 throughput 저하를 야기한다. 우리는 이 현상을 middle-phase thrashing으로 규정하며, 이는 장수명 agent가 시간이 지남에 따라 state를 누적할 때 cache 효율이 붕괴하는, 아직 충분히 규명되지 않은 병리 현상이다. 우리는 이러한 병리를 완화하려면 request 단위의 reactive한 cache 관리에서 벗어나, agent 수준의 proactive admission control로 나아가야 한다고 주장한다. 분산 시스템의 congestion control에서 영감을 받아, 우리는 KV cache를 피드백 기반 규제가 효율적 활용을 좌우하는 shared resource로 본다. 이 통찰을 바탕으로, 우리는 aggregate cache pressure를 제한하면서 execution continuity는 보존하는 agent admission 규제용 lightweight control layer인 PACE를 제안한다. PACE는 cache-aware control algorithm을 적응적으로 적용하여 runtime cache signal을 이용해 active agent 수를 동적으로 조절한다. 대규모 모델과 실제 agent workload 전반에서 PACE는 middle-phase thrashing을 방지하고 Qwen3-32B에서 최대 4.09×, DeepSeek-V3에서 1.90×까지 batch inference throughput을 향상시키며, 기존 LLM serving system과도 호환된다.</p>"},{"id":"65868","en":"Predictable Compression Failures: Order Sensitivity and Information Budgeting for Evidence-Grounded Binary Adjudication","ko":"예측 가능한 압축 실패: 증거 기반 이진 판정을 위한 순서 민감성과 정보 예산 편성","authors":"Leon Chlon, Ahmed Karim, MarcAntonio Awada","pos":"#1800","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=9HpQXq9e9W","abs":"Transformers used for evidence-grounded question answering with binary adjudication (e.g., support/refute or yes/no) can be highly sensitive to the order in which exchangeable evidence is presented, producing dispersion across permutations and unreliable attempted answers (“hallucinations” under a Bernoulli predicate). We treat evidence order as a nuisance variable and show that next-token training minimizes expected conditional description length over orderings, which can be close to Bayes-optimal in expectation while deviating under any fixed ordering. We quantify this expectation–realization gap via a Quantified Martingale Violation (QMV) bound that predicts $O(\\log n)$ growth in permutation dispersion under harmonic positional sensitivity. We then derive the Expectation-level Decompression Law (EDFL), relating expected information budget to achievable reliability for Bernoulli predicates, and use it to define Bits-to-Trust (B2T), Risk-of-Hallucination (RoH), and the Information Sufficiency Ratio (ISR), with a fixed ISR-gating rule for answer/abstain decisions under permutation mixtures. On 3,059 grounded items from a five-benchmark evidence-grounded QA suite (FEVER, HotpotQA, NQ-Open, PopQA, and Controls), we observe logarithmic dispersion and Jensen gains from uniform permutation mixtures. In a pre-specified held-out audit (528 items), an $ISR=1$ gate attains 0.0–0.7% hallucination with 20.6–27.9% abstention (95% CIs)."},{"id":"64626","en":"Mitigating Bias in Locally Constrained Decoding via Tractable Proposals","ko":"Tractable Proposal을 통한 지역적 제약 Decoding에서의 편향 완화","authors":"Meihua Dang, Linxin Song, Honghua Zhang, Jieyu Zhao, Guy Van den Broeck, Stefano Ermon","pos":"#1912","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=LYBs6f3jlK","abs":"Generations from large language models often fail to reliably conform to logical constraints such as JSON schema. Existing locally-constrained decoding (LCD) approaches enforce constraints by myopically masking out next tokens, resulting in biased sampling and degradation in downstream performance. Recent work introduces sequential Monte Carlo (SMC) methods to mitigate such sampling biases, but designing effective proposal distributions or potential functions remains a key challenge. In this work, we propose a generic approach to construct proposals and potentials for SMC sampling from $p_{\\texttt{lm}}( \\cdot \\mid \\texttt{constraint})$. First, we show that constraints specified as finite automata (FA) can be tensorized for efficient execution on GPUs, which we use to construct *globally-constrained decoding* (GCD) proposals. In addition, leveraging the fact that a tensorized FA shares the same *circuit structure* as hidden Markov models (HMM), we circuit-multiply it with an HMM to obtain the *probabilistic GCD* (P-GCD) proposal that encodes both logical and probabilistic information about the target distribution $p_{\\texttt{lm}}( \\cdot \\mid \\texttt{constraint})$. We evaluate (P-)GCD on xLAM, a widely adopted function-calling dataset, and on CommonGen, a keyword-based constrained generation benchmark. Experiments show that compared to LCD proposals, under the same SMC sampling setup, (P-)GCD achieve faster convergence to the target distribution with significantly fewer particles.","absKo":"대규모 language model의 생성 결과는 JSON schema와 같은 논리적 제약을 안정적으로 따르지 못하는 경우가 많다. 기존의 locally-constrained decoding (LCD) 접근은 다음 token을 myopic하게 masking out함으로써 제약을 강제하는데, 이로 인해 biased sampling과 downstream performance 저하가 발생한다. 최근 연구는 이러한 sampling bias를 완화하기 위해 sequential Monte Carlo (SMC) 방법을 도입했지만, 효과적인 proposal distribution이나 potential function을 설계하는 일은 여전히 핵심 과제이다. 본 연구에서는 $p_{\\texttt{lm}}( \\cdot \\mid \\texttt{constraint})$로부터의 SMC sampling을 위한 proposal과 potential을 구성하는 일반적인 접근법을 제안한다. 먼저, finite automata (FA)로 명시된 제약이 GPU에서 효율적으로 실행될 수 있도록 tensorize할 수 있음을 보이고, 이를 이용해 *globally-constrained decoding* (GCD) proposal을 구성한다. 또한 tensorized FA가 hidden Markov models (HMM)과 동일한 *circuit structure*를 공유한다는 점을 활용하여, 이를 HMM과 circuit-multiply함으로써 목표 분포 $p_{\\texttt{lm}}( \\cdot \\mid \\texttt{constraint})$에 대한 논리적 및 확률적 정보를 모두 인코딩하는 *probabilistic GCD* (P-GCD) proposal을 얻는다. 우리는 널리 사용되는 function-calling dataset인 xLAM과 keyword-based constrained generation benchmark인 CommonGen에서 (P-)GCD를 평가한다. 실험 결과는 동일한 SMC sampling setup에서 LCD proposal과 비교했을 때, (P-)GCD가 훨씬 적은 particle만으로 target distribution으로 더 빠르게 수렴함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"66051","en":"A Queueing-Theoretic Framework for Stability Analysis of LLM Inference with KV Cache Memory Constraints","ko":"KV Cache 메모리 제약 하에서 LLM 추론 안정성 분석을 위한 대기행렬 이론 프레임워크","authors":"Chengyi Nie, Nian Si, Zijie Zhou","pos":"#2301","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=7X91AAKL5B","abs":"<p>The rapid adoption of large language models (LLMs) has created significant challenges for efficient inference at scale. Unlike traditional workloads, LLM inference is constrained by both computation and the memory overhead of key–value (KV) caching, which accelerates decoding but quickly exhausts GPU memory. In this paper, we introduce the first queueing-theoretic framework that explicitly incorporates both computation and GPU memory constraints into the analysis of LLM inference. Based on this framework, we derive rigorous stability and instability conditions that determine whether an LLM inference service can sustain incoming demand without unbounded queue growth. This result offers a powerful tool for system deployment, potentially addressing the core challenge of GPU provisioning. By combining an estimated request arrival rate with our derived stable service rate, operators can calculate the necessary cluster size to avoid both costly over-purchasing and performance-violating under-provisioning. We further validate our theoretical predictions through extensive experiments in real GPU production environments. Our results show that the predicted stability conditions are highly accurate, with deviations typically within 10%.</p>"},{"id":"61101","en":"Variational Learning for Insertion-based Generation","ko":"삽입 기반 생성을 위한 Variational Learning","authors":"Yangtian Zhang, Zhe Wang, Arthur Gretton, ZHITAO YING, David van Dijk, Michalis Titsias, Jiaxin Shi","pos":"#2402","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=thVeEXPaSg","abs":"<p>Non-monotonic sequence generation methods, such as masked diffusion models, provide a flexible alternative to left-to-right autoregressive modeling by allowing tokens to be generated in non-fixed and prescribed orders. Despite their practical advantages, most existing non-monotonic models are order-agnostic and rely on a fixed-length masked token grid, limiting their ability to support variable-length generation and adaptive insertion order. In this work, we introduce a probabilistic framework for learning insertion order in variable-length insertion models. We formalize a bijective correspondence between insertion trajectories and permutations, which enables an exact reparameterization of the data likelihood as a sum over permutations. Building on this result, we propose the <strong>Insertion Process (IP)</strong>, a stochastic generative model that jointly learns <em>where</em> to insert, <em>what</em> to insert, and <em>when</em> to terminate, trained via permutation-based variational inference. Unlike prior masked or fixed-canvas approaches, IP natively supports variable-length generation and learns data-driven preferences over insertion orders. Experiments on planning benchmarks and molecular SMILES generation demonstrate that learning insertion order improves both modeling quality and generalization in domains without a canonical left-to-right structure.</p>","absKo":"<p>masked diffusion model과 같은 non-monotonic sequence generation method는 token을 고정되거나 미리 정해진 순서가 아닌 방식으로 생성할 수 있게 함으로써 left-to-right autoregressive modeling에 유연한 대안을 제공한다. 실용적 장점에도 불구하고, 기존의 대부분 non-monotonic model은 order-agnostic하며 고정 길이 masked token grid에 의존하므로 variable-length generation과 adaptive insertion order를 지원하는 능력이 제한된다. 본 연구에서는 variable-length insertion model에서 insertion order를 학습하기 위한 probabilistic framework를 제안한다. 우리는 insertion trajectory와 permutation 사이의 bijective correspondence를 정식화하며, 이를 통해 data likelihood를 permutation에 대한 합으로 정확히 재매개변수화할 수 있다. 이 결과를 바탕으로, 우리는 <strong>Insertion Process (IP)</strong>를 제안한다. IP는 <em>어디에</em> 삽입할지, <em>무엇을</em> 삽입할지, 그리고 <em>언제</em> 종료할지를 공동으로 학습하는 stochastic generative model이며, permutation-based variational inference로 학습된다. 기존의 masked 또는 fixed-canvas 접근법과 달리, IP는 variable-length generation을 자연스럽게 지원하고 insertion order에 대한 data-driven preference를 학습한다. planning benchmark와 molecular SMILES generation에서의 실험은 insertion order를 학습하는 것이 canonical left-to-right structure가 없는 도메인에서 modeling quality와 generalization 모두를 향상시킴을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"66125","en":"Fast and Expressive Multi-Byte Prediction with Probabilistic Circuits","ko":"확률 회로를 활용한 빠르고 표현력 있는 다중 바이트 예측","authors":"Andreas Grivas, Lorenzo Loconte, Emile van Krieken, Piotr Nawrot, Yu Zhao, Euan Wielewski, Pasquale Minervini, Edoardo Ponti, Antonio Vergari","pos":"#2607","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=6kCEyw9god","abs":"<p>Multi-token prediction (MTP) is a prominent strategy to significantly speed up generation in large language models (LLMs), especially in byte-level LLMs, which are tokeniser-free but prohibitively slow. However, existing MTP methods often sacrifice expressiveness by assuming independence between future tokens. In this work, we investigate the trade-off between expressiveness and latency in MTP within the framework of probabilistic circuits (PCs). Our framework, named MTPC, allows one to explore different ways to encode the joint distributions over future tokens by selecting different circuit architectures, generalising classical models such as (hierarchical) mixture models, hidden Markov models, and tensor networks. We show the efficacy of MTPC by retrofitting existing byte-level LLMs, such as EvaByte, and byte-fied subword models, such as Llama3.2 3B. Our experiments show that, when combined with speculative decoding, MTPC substantially speeds up generation compared to MTP with independence assumptions, while guaranteeing to retain the performance of the original verifier LLM. We also rigorously study the optimal trade-off between expressiveness and latency when exploring the possible parameterisations of MTPC, such as PC architectures and partial layer sharing between the verifier and draft LLMs.</p>"},{"id":"67233","en":"Position: Predictive Uncertainty Is Not Enough -- Joint Distribution for Full Uncertainty Representation","ko":"Position: 예측 불확실성만으로는 충분하지 않다 -- 완전한 불확실성 표현을 위한 결합 분포","authors":"Adria Aldoma, Unai Gurbindo, Axel Brando","pos":"#3106","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=59kGJTWGUv","abs":"When AI is deployed in safety-critical domains, erroneous and overconfident predictions can have severe consequences. Therefore, comprehensive uncertainty quantification (UQ) should be a foundational requirement for responsible decision-making. Current UQ methods based on epistemic and aleatoric decomposition have been found insufficient for fully understanding the problem. We add that this limitation is further compounded by the systematic isolation of these terms without considering uncertainty about the domain. Our position claims that any meaningful analysis must account for three sources of uncertainty -domain, epistemic, and aleatoric-, and that only the joint distribution $p(x,y|\\mathcal{D})$ provides a coherent representation of uncertainty.   We begin by mirroring prior findings that show the application of information-theoretic UQ methods to ID and OOD settings is suboptimal, primarily due to the inherent difficulty of disentangling epistemic and aleatoric components. Based on this, we support that modeling the unconditional distribution $p(x|\\mathcal{D})$ is required to account for input validity, resulting in a third class of uncertainty: \\emph{domain} uncertainty. Finally, by considering both the domain and the conditional distribution $p(y|x,\\mathcal{D})$, we argue that their product $p(x,y|\\mathcal{D})$ fully encapsulates all sources of uncertainty."},{"id":"61094","en":"VERA-V: Variational Inference Framework for Jailbreaking Vision-Language Models","ko":"VERA-V: Vision-Language Model Jailbreaking을 위한 Variational Inference 프레임워크","authors":"Qilin Liao, Anamika Lochab, Ruqi Zhang","pos":"#3500","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=tj9EwfaxHm","abs":"<p>Vision-Language Models (VLMs) extend large language models with visual reasoning, but their multimodal design also introduces new, underexplored vulnerabilities. Existing multimodal red-teaming methods largely rely on brittle templates, focus on single-attack settings, and expose only a narrow subset of vulnerabilities. To address these limitations, we introduce VERA-V, a variational inference framework that recasts multimodal jailbreak discovery as learning a joint posterior distribution over paired text-image prompts. This probabilistic view captures complex cross-modal interactions, enabling stealthy, coordinated adversarial inputs that bypass model guardrails. We train a lightweight attacker to approximate the posterior, allowing efficient sampling of diverse jailbreaks and providing distributional insights into vulnerabilities. VERA-V further integrates three complementary strategies: (i) typography-based text prompts that embed harmful cues, (ii) diffusion-based image synthesis that introduces adversarial signals, and (iii) structured distractors to fragment VLM attention. Experiments on HarmBench and HADES benchmarks show that VERA-V consistently outperforms state-of-the-art baselines on both open-source and frontier VLMs, achieving up to 53.75\\% higher attack success rate (ASR) over the best baseline on GPT-4o.</p>","absKo":"<p>Vision-Language Models (VLMs)는 large language models에 시각적 추론을 결합하지만, 이러한 multimodal 설계는 또한 새롭고 충분히 탐구되지 않은 취약점을 초래한다. 기존의 multimodal red-teaming 방법은 대체로 취약한 템플릿에 의존하고, 단일 공격 설정에 초점을 맞추며, 노출하는 취약점의 범위도 제한적이다. 이러한 한계를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 VERA-V를 제안한다. 이는 paired text-image prompts에 대한 joint posterior distribution 학습으로 multimodal jailbreak discovery를 재구성하는 variational inference framework이다. 이 probabilistic view는 복잡한 cross-modal interaction을 포착하여, model guardrails를 우회하는 은밀하고 coordinated adversarial input을 가능하게 한다. 우리는 posterior를 근사하도록 lightweight attacker를 학습시켜, 다양한 jailbreak를 효율적으로 sampling하고 취약성에 대한 distributional insight를 제공한다. VERA-V는 추가로 세 가지 상호보완적 전략을 통합한다: (i) harmful cue를 내포하는 typography-based text prompts, (ii) adversarial signals을 도입하는 diffusion-based image synthesis, (iii) VLM attention을 분절시키는 structured distractors. HarmBench와 HADES benchmark에서의 실험은 VERA-V가 open-source VLM과 frontier VLM 모두에서 state-of-the-art baseline을 일관되게 능가하며, GPT-4o에서 최상 baseline 대비 attack success rate (ASR)을 최대 53.75\\%까지 향상시킴을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"66495","en":"Split Group Knockoffs: Controlling False Discovery Rate in Transformational Group Sparsity","ko":"Split Group Knockoffs: 변환적 그룹 희소성에서 False Discovery Rate 제어","authors":"Siqi Chen, Yachen Gao, Yanwei Fu, Xinwei Sun","pos":"#3501","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=3BHfOvPcpG","abs":"<p>Controlling the false discovery rate (FDR) under complex sparsity structures remains a fundamental challenge in large language model (LLM) analysis. Motivated by multiple comparison problems in LLMs, we consider a setting in which sparsity arises at the group level after a linear transformation of model parameters. We propose Split Group Knockoffs (SGKs), a general framework for group-wise variable selection under grouped transformational sparsity that extends the Split Knockoff procedure to grouped transformed variables. We establish theoretical guarantees for group-level FDR control and support recovery consistency, addressing challenges induced by group-wise penalties in transformed spaces. Applying SGK to LLM behavior auditing experiment reveals that model disagreement is not uniform across subjects, but instead concentrates in domains with greater semantic and reasoning complexity, where SGK effectively distinguishes genuine behavioral deviations from surface-level performance variation.</p>"},{"id":"62074","en":"Latent Guided Sampling for Combinatorial Optimization","ko":"조합 최적화를 위한 잠재 가이드 샘플링","authors":"Sobihan Surendran, Adeline Fermanian, Sylvain Le Corff","pos":"#3502","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=k5xsXvNYQS","abs":"<p>Combinatorial Optimization problems are widespread in domains such as logistics, manufacturing, and drug discovery, yet their NP-hard nature makes them computationally challenging. Recent Neural Combinatorial Optimization (NCO) methods leverage deep learning to learn policies for constructing solutions, trained via Supervised or Reinforcement Learning. While promising, these approaches often rely on task-specific augmentations, perform poorly on out-of-distribution instances, and lack robust inference mechanisms. Moreover, existing latent space models either require labeled data or use an instance-independent latent distribution. In this work, we propose LGS-Net, a novel latent space model that conditions on problem instances, and introduce an efficient inference method, Latent Guided Sampling (LGS), based on Markov Chain Monte Carlo and Stochastic Approximation. We show that the iterations of our method form a time-inhomogeneous Markov Chain and provide rigorous theoretical convergence guarantees. Empirical results on benchmark routing tasks show that our method achieves state-of-the-art performance among NCO baselines.</p>","absKo":"<p>조합 최적화(Combinatorial Optimization) 문제는 물류, 제조, 약물 발견과 같은 분야 전반에 널리 존재하지만, NP-hard한 성질 때문에 계산적으로 매우 어렵다. 최근 Neural Combinatorial Optimization(NCO) 방법들은 deep learning을 활용해 해를 구성하는 정책을 학습하며, Supervised Learning 또는 Reinforcement Learning을 통해 훈련된다. 유망함에도 불구하고, 이러한 접근은 종종 task-specific augmentation에 의존하고, out-of-distribution 인스턴스에서 성능이 좋지 않으며, 강건한 inference 메커니즘이 부족하다. 또한 기존 latent space model은 labeled data를 요구하거나 instance-independent latent distribution을 사용한다. 본 연구에서는 문제 인스턴스에 조건화하는 새로운 latent space model인 LGS-Net을 제안하고, Markov Chain Monte Carlo와 Stochastic Approximation에 기반한 효율적인 inference 방법 Latent Guided Sampling(LGS)을 소개한다. 우리는 본 방법의 반복 과정이 time-inhomogeneous Markov Chain을 이룬다는 것을 보이고, 엄밀한 이론적 수렴 보장을 제공한다. benchmark routing task에 대한 실험 결과, 본 방법이 NCO baseline들 가운데 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성함을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"65688","en":"Testing For Distribution Shifts with Conditional Conformal Test Martingales","ko":"조건부 Conformal 검정 마팅게일을 통한 분포 이동 검정","authors":"Shalev Shaer, Yarin Bar, Drew Prinster, Yaniv Romano","pos":"#3505","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=B8sTBdGvqG","abs":"<p>We propose a sequential test for distribution-shift detection that allows conformal test martingales (CTMs) to work under a fixed, reference-conditional setting. Existing CTM detectors construct test martingales by continually growing a reference set with each incoming sample, using it to assess how atypical the new sample is relative to past observations. While this design yields anytime-valid type-I error control, it suffers from test-time contamination: after a change, post-shift observations enter the reference set and dilute the evidence for distribution shift, increasing detection delay and reducing power.  In contrast, our method avoids contamination by design by comparing each new sample to a fixed null reference dataset. Our main technical contribution is a robust martingale construction that remains valid conditional on the null reference data, achieved by explicitly accounting for the estimation error in the reference distribution induced by the finite reference set. This yields anytime-valid type-I error control together with guarantees of asymptotic power one and bounded expected detection delay. Empirically, our method detects shifts faster than standard CTMs, providing a powerful and reliable distribution-shift detector.</p>"},{"id":"62582","en":"Should I Have Expressed a Different Intent? Counterfactual Generation for LLM-Based Autonomous Control","ko":"다른 의도를 표현했어야 했을까? LLM 기반 자율 제어를 위한 반사실적 생성","authors":"Amirmohammad Farzaneh, Salvatore D&amp;#x27;oro, Osvaldo Simeone","pos":"#3506","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=fKsDQLjyIb","abs":"<p>Large language model (LLM)-powered agents can translate high-level user intents into plans and actions in an environment. Yet after observing an outcome, users may wonder: What if I had phrased my intent differently? We introduce a framework that enables such counterfactual reasoning in agentic LLM-driven control scenarios, while providing formal reliability guarantees. Our approach models the closed-loop interaction between a user, an LLM-based agent, and an environment as a structural causal model (SCM), and leverages test-time scaling to generate multiple candidate counterfactual outcomes via probabilistic abduction. Through an offline calibration phase, the proposed conformal counterfactual generation (CCG) yields sets of counterfactual outcomes that are guaranteed to contain the true counterfactual outcome with high probability. We showcase the performance of CCG on a wireless network control use case, demonstrating significant advantages compared to naive re-execution baselines.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large language model (LLM) 기반 agent는 고수준의 사용자 intent를 environment 내 plan과 action으로 변환할 수 있다. 그러나 결과를 관찰한 뒤 사용자는 이렇게 생각할 수 있다: 내가 intent를 다르게 표현했다면 어떻게 되었을까? 우리는 이러한 counterfactual reasoning을 agentic LLM-driven control scenario에서 가능하게 하면서도 formal reliability guarantee를 제공하는 framework를 소개한다. 우리의 접근은 사용자, LLM 기반 agent, environment 간의 closed-loop interaction을 structural causal model (SCM)로 모델링하고, test-time scaling을 활용하여 probabilistic abduction을 통해 여러 개의 candidate counterfactual outcome을 생성한다. offline calibration phase를 통해 제안하는 conformal counterfactual generation (CCG)은 true counterfactual outcome을 높은 확률로 포함하는 counterfactual outcome 집합을 산출한다는 보장을 제공한다. 우리는 wireless network control use case에서 CCG의 성능을 보여주며, naive re-execution baseline과 비교해 유의미한 장점을 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"61301","en":"MIRA: A Score for Conditional Distribution Accuracy and Model Comparison","ko":"MIRA: 조건부 분포 정확도와 모델 비교를 위한 점수","authors":"Sammy Sharief, Justine Zeghal, Gabriel Missael Barco, Pablo Lemos, Yashar Hezaveh, Laurence Perreault-Levasseur","pos":"#3507","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ra2t1V4nml","abs":"<p>We present Mira, a method for estimating the expected probability that samples from a candidate conditional distribution match the true, unknown conditional distribution, for which only data-label pairs are available. We derive theoretical bounds obtained when the candidate distribution matches the true one and when the conditional distributions are independent. This framework thus enables model comparison by quantifying the alignment between the conditional distribution of a candidate model and the data-label pairs of the true model. Consequently, Mira enables Bayesian model comparison through direct posterior validation, bypassing the challenging evidence computation. We demonstrate its effectiveness across several toy problems and Bayesian inference tasks.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 후보 conditional distribution에서 나온 sample이, data-label pair만 주어졌을 때의 true unknown conditional distribution과 일치할 것으로 기대되는 확률을 추정하는 방법인 Mira를 제시합니다. 우리는 후보 분포가 진짜 분포와 일치할 때와 conditional distribution이 독립일 때 얻어지는 theoretical bound를 유도합니다. 따라서 이 framework는 후보 model의 conditional distribution과 true model의 data-label pair 사이의 alignment를 정량화함으로써 model comparison을 가능하게 합니다. 결과적으로 Mira는 evidence computation의 어려움을 우회하면서 direct posterior validation을 통해 Bayesian model comparison을 가능하게 합니다. 우리는 여러 toy problem과 Bayesian inference task에서 그 효과를 입증합니다.</p>"},{"id":"61172","en":"Extending Prediction-Powered Inference through Conformal Prediction","ko":"Conformal Prediction을 통한 Prediction-Powered Inference 확장","authors":"Daniel Csillag, Pedro Dall’Antonia, Claudio Struchiner, Guilherme Tegoni Goedert","pos":"#3508","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=t3PXkjuTqe","abs":"<p>Prediction-powered inference is a recent methodology for the safe use of black-box ML models to impute missing data, strengthening inference of statistical parameters. However, many applications require strong properties besides valid inference, such as privacy, robustness or validity under continuous distribution shifts; deriving prediction-powered methods with such guarantees is generally an arduous process, and has to be done case by case. In this paper, we resolve this issue by connecting prediction-powered inference with conformal prediction: by performing imputation through a calibrated set-predictor, we attain validity while achieving additional guarantees in a natural manner. We instantiate our procedure for the inference of means, Z- and M-estimation, as well as e-values and e-value-based procedures. Furthermore, in the case of e-values, ours is the first general prediction-powered procedure that operates off-line. We demonstrate these advantages by applying our method on private and time-series data. Both tasks are nontrivial within the standard prediction-powered framework but become natural under our method.</p>","absKo":"<p>Prediction-powered inference는 black-box ML model을 사용해 missing data를 impute하고, statistical parameter에 대한 inference를 강화하기 위한 최근의 방법론이다. 그러나 많은 응용에서는 유효한 inference 외에도 privacy, robustness, continuous distribution shift 하에서의 validity 같은 강한 성질이 필요하다. 이러한 보장을 갖는 prediction-powered method를 도출하는 것은 일반적으로 매우 까다롭고, 사례별로 따로 수행해야 한다. 본 논문에서는 prediction-powered inference를 conformal prediction과 연결함으로써 이 문제를 해결한다. calibrated set-predictor를 통해 imputation을 수행하면, validity를 확보하는 동시에 자연스럽게 추가 보장도 달성할 수 있다. 우리는 mean inference, Z- 및 M-estimation, 그리고 e-value 및 e-value 기반 procedure에 이 방법을 적용한다. 더 나아가 e-value의 경우, 우리의 방법은 오프라인으로 동작하는 최초의 general prediction-powered procedure이다. 우리는 private data와 time-series data에 이 방법을 적용하여 이러한 장점을 보인다. 두 과제 모두 standard prediction-powered framework에서는 다루기 까다롭지만, 우리의 방법에서는 자연스럽게 처리된다.</p>"},{"id":"62478","en":"Expectation Consistency Loss: Rethink Confidence Calibration under Covariate Shift","ko":"Expectation Consistency Loss: Covariate Shift 하의 Confidence Calibration 재고","authors":"Jinzong Dong, Zhaohui Jiang, Bo Yang","pos":"#3509","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=gFPPTokv9C","abs":"Confidence calibration for classification models is vital in safety-critical decision-making scenarios and has received extensive attention. General confidence calibration methods assume training and test data are independent and identically distributed ($i.i.d.$), limiting their effectiveness under covariate shifts. Previous calibration methods under covariate shift struggle with class-wise or canonical calibrations and often rely on unstable importance weighting when density ratios are large or unbounded. Given the above limitations, this paper rethinks confidence calibration under covariate shifts. First, we derive a necessary and sufficient condition for confidence calibration under covariate shifts, named Expectation consistency condition, which reveals covariate shifts do not necessarily lead to uncalibrated confidence and provides a weaker condition for confidence calibration than global covariate distribution alignment. Then, utilizing Expectation consistency condition, this paper proposes an unsupervised domain adaptation loss to calibrate confidence of the target domain, named Expectation consistency loss (ECL), which is compatible with canonical calibration, class-wise calibration, and top-label calibration. Third, we prove that computing ECL loss has the same sample complexity as Expected Calibration Error (ECE) and provide a theoretically grounded mini-batch trainable scheme for ECL loss. Finally, we validate the effectiveness of our method on both simulated and real-world covariate shift datasets.","absKo":"분류 모델의 confidence calibration은 safety-critical decision-making 시나리오에서 매우 중요하며, 이에 대해 광범위한 관심이 집중되어 왔다. 일반적인 confidence calibration 방법은 training data와 test data가 independent and identically distributed ($i.i.d.$)라고 가정하므로, covariate shift 하에서는 효과가 제한된다. covariate shift 하의 기존 calibration 방법은 class-wise 또는 canonical calibration에서 어려움을 겪고, density ratio가 크거나 unbounded일 때 불안정한 importance weighting에 의존하는 경우가 많다. 이러한 한계를 바탕으로, 본 논문은 covariate shift 하의 confidence calibration을 새롭게 재고한다. 먼저, 우리는 covariate shift 하에서 confidence calibration을 위한 필요충분조건을 유도하고 이를 Expectation consistency condition이라 명명한다. 이는 covariate shift가 반드시 uncalibrated confidence로 이어지는 것은 아님을 밝히며, 전역적인 covariate distribution alignment보다 더 약한 조건을 confidence calibration의 기준으로 제시한다. 다음으로, Expectation consistency condition을 활용하여 target domain의 confidence를 calibrate하기 위한 unsupervised domain adaptation loss를 제안하는데, 이를 Expectation consistency loss (ECL)이라 부른다. 이 loss는 canonical calibration, class-wise calibration, top-label calibration과 모두 호환된다. 셋째, ECL loss를 계산하는 데 필요한 sample complexity가 Expected Calibration Error (ECE)와 동일함을 증명하고, 이론적으로 근거 있는 mini-batch trainable scheme을 제시한다. 마지막으로, 시뮬레이션과 실제 covariate shift dataset 모두에서 제안 방법의 효과를 검증한다."},{"id":"62728","en":"An Efficient Joint Learning Approach for Item Response Theory","ko":"IRT를 위한 효율적 Joint Learning 접근","authors":"Tanish Agarwal, Kaustubh Shivshankar Shejole, Arpit Agarwal","pos":"#3511","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=dtbYmM1rHR","abs":"Item response theory (IRT) is widely used in areas such as recommender systems, education, psychology, and other fields. A popular model for IRT is the Rasch model. Under this model, if a user with ability $\\theta$ performs a task with difficulty $\\beta$ then its label $X \\sim \\text{Bernoulli} (1 /  (1 + \\exp(-(\\theta - \\beta)))$. Existing joint maximum likelihood estimation approaches for this problem do not perform well on small datasets and also lack theoretical guarantees. Recently, Nguyen and Zhang proposed a two step approach: (1) spectral method for estimation of task parameters, (2) likelihood optimization for estimation of user parameters. While this approach is theoretically sound, it is not computationally efficient. In this work, we propose an EM-based algorithm for joint estimation of item and user parameters by introducing Pólya-Gamma latent variables, which simplify the logistic log-likelihood. We show that our algorithm is both theoretically sound and consistently outperforms existing methods on synthetic and real-world datasets.","absKo":"Item response theory (IRT)는 recommender system, education, psychology 및 기타 분야에서 널리 사용된다. IRT의 대표적인 model은 Rasch model이다. 이 model에서 ability가 $\\theta$인 user가 difficulty가 $\\beta$인 task를 수행하면 그 label은 $X \\sim \\text{Bernoulli} (1 /  (1 + \\exp(-(\\theta - \\beta))))$를 따른다. 이 문제에 대한 기존의 joint maximum likelihood estimation 접근법은 작은 dataset에서 성능이 좋지 않고, 이론적 보장도 부족하다. 최근 Nguyen과 Zhang은 두 단계 접근법을 제안했다: (1) task parameter 추정을 위한 spectral method, (2) user parameter 추정을 위한 likelihood optimization. 이 접근법은 이론적으로 타당하지만, 계산 효율은 높지 않다. 본 연구에서는 logistic log-likelihood를 단순화하는 Pólya-Gamma latent variable을 도입하여 item 및 user parameter의 joint estimation을 위한 EM 기반 algorithm을 제안한다. 우리는 우리의 algorithm이 이론적으로 타당하며 synthetic 및 real-world dataset에서 기존 방법들을 일관되게 상회함을 보인다."},{"id":"62423","en":"Variational Learning of Disentangled Representations","ko":"Disentangled Representation의 Variational Learning","authors":"Yuli Slavutsky, Ozgur Beker, David Blei, Bianca Dumitrascu","pos":"#3512","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=gl6N1mfe5t","abs":"<p>Disentangled representations separate factors that are shared across conditions from those that are condition-specific. Such separation is needed for generalization to new domains, treatments, patients, or species. A dominant line of work pursues this goal through variational formulations. While these approaches achieve partial disentanglement, they often exhibit three common limitations: they either do not remove all condition-specific information from the shared representation, allow the shared representation to become uninformative, or impose independence assumptions that do not reflect the underlying generative process. In this work, we introduce DisCoVR, a variational framework that addresses these limitations. Its objective is aligned with the probabilistic structure of the data-generating process, and includes an adversarial term that prevents condition-specific information from being encoded in the shared representation. DisCoVR reconstructs the data from both shared and condition-specific representations, ensuring that each remains informative, and uses a structured prior that further reinforces the informativeness of both representations. We show that across synthetic, image, and single-cell RNA-sequencing datasets, DisCoVR achieves stronger disentanglement compared to previous approaches.</p>","absKo":"조건 간에 공유되는 요인과 condition-specific한 요인을 분리하는 것이 disentangled representation의 목표이다. 이러한 분리는 새로운 domain, treatment, patient, 또는 species로의 generalization에 필요하다. 이 목표를 추구하는 대표적인 흐름은 variational formulation을 사용한다. 이 접근법들은 부분적인 disentanglement를 달성하지만, 종종 세 가지 공통된 한계를 보인다: shared representation에서 모든 condition-specific information을 제거하지 못하거나, shared representation이 정보가 없게 되거나, 혹은 underlying generative process를 반영하지 않는 independence assumption을 부과한다. 본 연구에서는 이러한 한계를 해결하는 variational framework인 DisCoVR를 소개한다. 그 objective는 data-generating process의 probabilistic structure와 정렬되어 있으며, shared representation에 condition-specific information이 인코딩되는 것을 막는 adversarial term을 포함한다. DisCoVR는 shared representation과 condition-specific representation 모두로부터 데이터를 reconstruct하여 각각이 충분히 informative하도록 보장하고, 두 representation의 informativeness를 추가로 강화하는 structured prior를 사용한다. synthetic, image, single-cell RNA-sequencing dataset 전반에서 DisCoVR가 이전 접근법보다 더 강한 disentanglement를 달성함을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"66533","en":"Noisy-Channel Minimum Bayes Risk Decoding","ko":"잡음 채널 최소 Bayes 위험 디코딩","authors":"Yusuke Sakai, Hidetaka Kamigaito, Taro Watanabe","pos":"#3513","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=2qNpTcsu7l","abs":"<p>Minimum Bayes Risk (MBR) decoding yields more robust and higher-quality text generation than maximum a posteriori (MAP) decoding by selecting hypotheses that maximize expected utility over sampled pseudo-references. However, there exists discrepancy in the design: hypothesis selection calculates expected utility scores conditioned on given pseudo-references, while commonly used evaluation metrics, e.g., BLEU and COMET, are asymmetric. Therefore, it is important to consider both hypothesis-to-reference and reference-to-hypothesis directional effects. In this study, we introduce a noisy channel decomposition of MBR decoding that naturally incorporates bidirectional effects to account for these asymmetries. We decompose MBR decoding into four interacting components: hypothesis-to-reference likelihood, reference-to-hypothesis likelihood, hypothesis prior, and reference prior. This decomposition provides a unified interpretation of existing MBR variants and enables metric- and task-specific interpretability by isolating the contribution of each channel. Furthermore, our comprehensive analysis demonstrates that appropriate channel weighting consistently yields performance gains over original MBR decoding across tasks and utility functions.</p>"},{"id":"60915","en":"Joint Model and Data Sparsification via the Marginal Likelihood","ko":"Marginal Likelihood를 통한 모델과 데이터의 공동 Sparsification","authors":"Alexander Timans, Thomas Moellenhoff, Christian Andersson Naesseth, Mohammad Emtiyaz Khan, Eric Nalisnick","pos":"#3514","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=vMcu1h3fOV","abs":"<p>Sparse recovery in linear systems underpins applications from signal processing to high-dimensional regression. Sparse Bayesian Learning, grounded in the principle of automatic relevance determination (ARD), offers a practical Bayesian mechanism for feature sparsity via marginal likelihood optimization. Yet, its reliance on a homoscedastic noise model renders it sensitive to data contaminations such as outliers or misspecified noise, harming model fit and predictions. Instead, we propose jointly learning individual feature and sample relevancies, enabling simultaneous model and data sparsification via a single Bayesian objective. This symmetric pruning of model and data offers a natural extension that preserves conjugacy, admits closed-form updates for standard optimization procedures, and aligns with perspectives from robust regression and influence functions. Empirical results across diverse regression tasks affirm that a joint ARD approach consistently yields both sparse and robust prediction models.</p>","absKo":"<p>선형 시스템에서의 sparse recovery는 signal processing에서 고차원 회귀에 이르기까지 다양한 응용의 기반이 된다. automatic relevance determination (ARD) 원리에 기반한 Sparse Bayesian Learning은 marginal likelihood optimization을 통해 feature sparsity를 구현하는 실용적인 Bayesian 메커니즘을 제공한다. 그러나 homoscedastic noise model에 의존하기 때문에 outlier나 misspecified noise 같은 데이터 오염에 민감하며, 이로 인해 model fit과 prediction 성능이 저하된다. 이에 우리는 개별 feature와 sample relevance를 함께 학습하여, 단일 Bayesian objective로 model과 data를 동시에 sparsify하는 방법을 제안한다. model과 data에 대한 이러한 대칭적 pruning은 conjugacy를 보존하고, 표준 optimization 절차에 대해 closed-form update를 허용하며, robust regression 및 influence function 관점과도 부합하는 자연스러운 확장이다. 다양한 회귀 task에 대한 실험 결과는 joint ARD 접근이 일관되게 sparse하면서도 robust한 prediction model을 산출함을 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"63737","en":"De-Linearizing Agent Traces: Bayesian Inference of Latent Partial Orders for Efficient Execution","ko":"Agent Trace 비선형화: 효율적 실행을 위한 잠재 부분순서의 베이지안 추론","authors":"Dongqing Li, Zheqiao Cheng, Geoff Nicholls, Quyu Kong","pos":"#3615","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=UAXQW194WT","abs":"<p>AI agents increasingly execute procedural workflows as sequential action traces, which obscures latent concurrency and induces repeated step-by-step reasoning. We introduce BPOP, a Bayesian framework that infers a latent dependency partial order from noisy linearized traces. BPOP models traces as stochastic linear extensions of an underlying graph and performs efficient MCMC inference via a tractable frontier-softmax likelihood that avoids #P-hard marginalization over linear extensions. We evaluate on our open-sourced Cloud-IaC-6, a suite of cloud provisioning tasks with heterogeneous LLM-generated traces, and WFCommons scientific workflows. BPOP recovers dependency structure more accurately than trace-only and process-mining baselines, and the inferred graphs support a compiled executor that prunes irrelevant context, yielding substantial reductions in token usage and execution time.</p>","absKo":"AI agent는 점점 더 procedural workflow를 순차적 action trace로 실행하고 있으며, 이로 인해 latent concurrency가 가려지고 반복적인 step-by-step reasoning이 유발된다. 우리는 noisy하게 linearized된 trace로부터 latent dependency partial order를 추론하는 Bayesian framework인 BPOP을 제안한다. BPOP은 trace를 underlying graph의 stochastic linear extension으로 모델링하고, linear extension에 대한 #P-hard marginalization을 피하는 tractable frontier-softmax likelihood를 통해 효율적인 MCMC inference를 수행한다. 우리는 다양한 LLM-generated trace를 포함한 cloud provisioning task 모음인 오픈소스 Cloud-IaC-6과 WFCommons scientific workflow에서 평가한다. BPOP은 trace-only 및 process-mining baseline보다 dependency structure를 더 정확하게 복원하며, 추론된 graph는 불필요한 context를 제거하는 compiled executor를 지원하여 token usage와 execution time을 크게 줄인다.</p>"},{"id":"64618","en":"Copula-SVI: Vine-Copula Variational Inference for Instance-Level Correlation Capturing","ko":"Copula-SVI: 인스턴스 수준 상관관계 포착을 위한 Vine-Copula 변분 추론","authors":"Junxi Xiao, Qinliang Su","pos":"#4503","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=LeAekHRHLZ","abs":"<p>Mean-field variational inference (VI) is scalable, but its independence assumption can severely limit inference when the posterior is inherently coupled across instances especially for correlated data. Existing structured VI approaches either impose simple dependence patterns or incur substantial cost as dependence becomes richer, leaving efficient higher-order instance-level dependence modeling largely unresolved. We propose Copula-SVI, which augments amortized marginals with an explicit vine-copula posterior and refines joint samples with Stein updates toward the true posterior. The vine construction makes dependence learning and sampling practical by decomposing it into bivariate copula factors, enabling edge-minibatched training with variance-aware level-wise sampling and efficient dependence-aware initialization via a sparse vine built from the same sampled edges. Experiments on constrained clustering and time series modeling show consistent improvements over strong structured VI baselines and demonstrate efficient higher-order instance-level dependence modeling.</p>","absKo":"<p>mean-field variational inference (VI)는 확장성이 뛰어나지만, 독립성 가정은 posterior가 본질적으로 instance 간 결합(coupled)되어 있을 때, 특히 correlated data에서 추론을 심각하게 제한할 수 있다. 기존의 structured VI 접근법은 단순한 dependence pattern을 강제하거나, dependence가 더 풍부해질수록 상당한 비용을 초래하여, 효율적인 higher-order instance-level dependence modeling은 여전히 크게 해결되지 않은 상태로 남아 있다. 우리는 amortized marginal에 명시적인 vine-copula posterior를 추가하고, Stein update를 통해 joint sample을 true posterior 쪽으로 정련하는 Copula-SVI를 제안한다. vine construction은 dependence learning과 sampling을 bivariate copula factor로 분해함으로써 실용적으로 만들어 주며, 같은 sampled edge를 기반으로 한 sparse vine을 통해 variance-aware level-wise sampling과 효율적인 dependence-aware initialization을 가능하게 한다. constrained clustering과 time series modeling에 대한 실험은 강력한 structured VI baseline 대비 일관된 개선을 보이며, 효율적인 higher-order instance-level dependence modeling을 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"63574","en":"Betting on Predictions","ko":"예측에 베팅하기","authors":"Yaniv Tenzer, Elad Tolochinksy, Yaniv Romano","pos":"#4504","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Vt0tmqhfDM","abs":"We introduce a testing-by-betting framework that leverages predictions on unlabeled data to enhance the power of sequential hypothesis testing. Given limited samples from the joint distribution of $(X,Y)$, and additional unlabeled samples from the marginal of $X$, we ask how unlabeled data can be used to hypothesize about the distribution of $Y$, and the conditional distribution of $Y\\mid X$. We introduce an e-statistic and use it to construct a sequential test. Under standard distributional assumptions---label shift or concept shift---we establish that the test is anytime valid. Furthermore, we show that for binary data, the e-statistic has non-trivial power. Crucially, our approach retains these properties even when the underlying predictions are inaccurate.  Through simulations and applications to large language models evaluation, we demonstrate power gains over baseline approaches, including prediction-powered inference. These gains persist even with relatively limited unlabeled data and when predictions have low accuracy due to weak correlation between $X$ and $Y$.","absKo":"라벨이 없는 데이터에 대한 예측을 활용해 sequential hypothesis testing의 power를 높이는 testing-by-betting framework를 제안한다. $(X,Y)$의 joint distribution에서 제한된 sample과 $X$의 marginal에서 추가 unlabeled sample이 주어졌을 때, unlabeled data를 어떻게 $Y$의 distribution과 $Y\\mid X$의 conditional distribution에 대한 가설 설정에 활용할 수 있는지 묻는다. 우리는 e-statistic을 도입하고 이를 사용해 sequential test를 구성한다. 표준 distributional assumption인 label shift 또는 concept shift 하에서, 이 test가 anytime valid임을 보인다. 또한 binary data의 경우 e-statistic이 비자명한 power를 가진다는 점을 보인다. 중요한 것은, underlying prediction이 부정확하더라도 이 접근법이 이러한 성질을 유지한다는 점이다. 시뮬레이션과 large language model 평가에의 적용을 통해, prediction-powered inference를 포함한 baseline 접근법보다 더 큰 power를 보임을 입증한다. 이러한 향상은 unlabeled data가 비교적 제한적일 때와 $X$와 $Y$의 상관이 약해 prediction accuracy가 낮을 때에도 지속된다."},{"id":"65150","en":"Inverting Data Transformations via Diffusion Sampling","ko":"Diffusion 샘플링을 통한 데이터 변환 역전","authors":"Jinwoo Kim, Sékou-Oumar Kaba, Jiyun Park, Seunghoon Hong, Siamak Ravanbakhsh","pos":"#2917","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=GK89Mi6ZRf","abs":"<p>We study the problem of transformation inversion on general Lie groups: a datum is transformed by an unknown group element, and the goal is to recover an inverse transformation that maps it back to the original data distribution. We take a probabilistic view and model the posterior over transformations as a Boltzmann distribution defined by an energy function on data space. To sample from this posterior, we introduce a diffusion process on Lie groups that keeps all updates on-manifold and only requires computations in the associated Lie alge- bra. Our method, Transformation-Inverting Energy Diffusion (TIED), relies on a new trivialized target-score identity that enables efficient score-based sampling of the transformation posterior. As a key application, we focus on test-time equivariance, where the objective is to improve the robustness of pretrained neural networks to input transformations. Experiments on image homographies and PDE symmetries demonstrate that TIED can restore transformed inputs to the training distribution at test time, showing improved performance over strong canonicalization and sampling baselines.</p>"},{"id":"65168","en":"Discrete Adjoint Schrödinger Bridge Sampler","ko":"이산 Adjoint Schrödinger Bridge 샘플러","authors":"Wei Guo, Yuchen Zhu, Xiaochen Du, Juno Nam, Yongxin Chen, Rafael Gomez-Bombarelli, Guan-Horng Liu, Molei Tao, Jaemoo Choi","pos":"#3503","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=G9KydTWzZL","abs":"<p>Learning discrete neural samplers is challenging due to the lack of gradients and combinatorial complexity. While stochastic optimal control (SOC) and Schrödinger bridge (SB) provide principled solutions, efficient SOC solvers like adjoint matching (AM), which excel in continuous domains, remain unexplored for discrete spaces. We bridge this gap by revealing that the core mechanism of AM is <em>state-space agnostic</em>, and introduce <strong>discrete ASBS</strong>, a unified framework that extends AM and adjoint Schrödinger bridge sampler (ASBS) to discrete spaces. Theoretically, we analyze the optimality conditions of the discrete SB problem and its connection to SOC, identifying a necessary cyclic group structure on the state space to enable this extension. Empirically, discrete ASBS achieves competitive sample quality with significant advantages in training efficiency and scalability.</p>"},{"id":"65494","en":"Can Microcanonical Langevin Dynamics Leverage Mini-Batch Gradient Noise?","ko":"Microcanonical Langevin Dynamics는 미니 배치 그래디언트 노이즈를 활용할 수 있는가?","authors":"Emanuel Sommer, Kangning Diao, Jakob Robnik, Uros Seljak, David Rügamer","pos":"#3504","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=D2evvc90tF","abs":"<p>Scaling inference methods such as Markov chain Monte Carlo to high-dimensional models remains a central challenge in Bayesian deep learning. A promising recent proposal, microcanonical Langevin Monte Carlo, has shown state-of-the-art performance across a wide range of problems. However, its reliance on full-dataset gradients makes it prohibitively expensive for large-scale problems. This paper addresses a fundamental question: Can microcanonical dynamics effectively leverage mini-batch gradient noise? We provide the first systematic study of this problem, establishing a novel continuous-time theoretical analysis of stochastic-gradient microcanonical dynamics. We reveal two critical failure modes: a theoretically derived bias due to anisotropic gradient noise and numerical instabilities in complex high-dimensional posteriors. To tackle these issues, we propose a principled gradient noise preconditioning scheme shown to significantly reduce this bias and develop a novel, energy-variance-based adaptive tuner that automates step size selection and dynamically informs numerical guardrails. The resulting algorithm is a robust and scalable microcanonical Monte Carlo sampler that achieves state-of-the-art performance on challenging high-dimensional inference tasks like Bayesian neural networks. Combined with recent ensemble techniques, our work unlocks a new class of stochastic microcanonical Langevin ensemble (SMILE) samplers for large-scale Bayesian inference.</p>"},{"id":"65830","en":"ProcMEM: Learning Reusable Procedural Memory from Experience via Non-Parametric PPO for LLM Agents","ko":"ProcMEM: LLM 에이전트를 위한 비모수적 PPO를 통한 경험으로부터 재사용 가능한 절차적 메모리 학습","authors":"QIRUI MI, Zhijian Ma, Mengyue Yang, Yisen Wang, Haoxuan Li, Haifeng Zhang, Jun Wang","pos":"#3916","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=9kJQjx2B80","abs":"<p>LLM-driven agents demonstrate strong performance in sequential decision-making but often rely on on-the-fly reasoning, re-deriving solutions even in recurring scenarios. This insufficient experience reuse leads to computational redundancy and execution instability. To bridge this gap, we propose ProcMEM, a framework that enables agents to autonomously learn procedural memory from interaction experiences without parameter updates. By formalizing a Skill-MDP, ProcMEM transforms passive episodic narratives into executable Skills defined by activation, execution, and termination conditions to ensure executability.  To achieve reliable reusability without capability degradation, we introduce Non-Parametric PPO, which leverages semantic gradients for high-quality candidate generation and a PPO Gate for robust Skill verification. Through score-based maintenance, ProcMEM sustains compact, high-quality procedural memory. Experimental results across in-domain, cross-task, and cross-agent scenarios demonstrate that ProcMEM achieves \\textbf{superior reuse rates and significant performance gains} with extreme memory compression. Visualized evolutionary trajectories and Skill distributions further reveal how ProcMEM transparently accumulates, refines, and reuses procedural knowledge to facilitate long-term autonomy.</p>"},{"id":"64058","en":"HiPER: Hierarchical Plan–Execute RL for Multi-Turn LLM Agents","ko":"HiPER: 멀티턴 LLM 에이전트를 위한 계층적 계획-실행 RL","authors":"Jiangweizhi Peng, Yuanxin Liu, Ruida Zhou, Charles Fleming, Zhaoran Wang, Alfredo Garcia, Mingyi Hong","pos":"#111","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=RJWQcgd3hX","abs":"<p>Training LLMs as interactive agents for multi-turn decision-making remains challenging, particularly in long-horizon tasks with sparse and delayed rewards, where agents must execute extended sequences of actions before receiving meaningful feedback. Most existing reinforcement learning (RL) methods model LLM agents as <em>flat</em> policies operating at a single time scale, selecting an action at each turn. In sparse-reward settings, this forces the agent to infer long-range dependencies solely from distant end-of-trajectory signals, often leading to inefficient learning and unstable behavior in complex environments.  We propose <strong>HiPER</strong>, a novel <strong>Hi</strong>erarchical <strong>P</strong>lan–<strong>E</strong>xecute <strong>R</strong>L framework that jointly models and optimizes high-level subgoal planning and low-level action execution for LLM agents to overcome flat RL's brittle long-horizon behavior and weak credit assignment under sparse outcome feedback. By maintaining persistent subgoals across multiple turns and explicitly deciding when to switch between them, HiPER introduces structured intermediate decision points that facilitate learning under sparse feedback, converting implicit multi-turn structure into learnable decisions at different time scales. To enable effective training, we introduce Hierarchical Advantage Estimation (HAE), a two-timescale policy gradient method that assigns credit to both action execution and subgoal transitions and achieves variance reduction relative to flat advantage estimation.  Empirically, HiPER achieves state-of-the-art performance on challenging interactive benchmarks, reaching 97.4\\% success on ALFWorld (+6.6\\% over the best prior method) and 83.3\\% on WebShop, with especially large gains on long-horizon tasks requiring multiple dependent subtasks. These results highlight the importance of explicit hierarchical decomposition for scalable RL training of multi-turn LLM agents.</p>","absKo":"<p>LLM을 multi-turn decision-making을 수행하는 interactive agent로 학습하는 일은 여전히 어렵다. 특히 긴 horizon의 작업처럼 sparse하고 지연된 reward 환경에서는 agent가 의미 있는 피드백을 받기 전에 긴 action sequence를 수행해야 하므로 더욱 그러하다. 기존의 대부분 reinforcement learning(RL) 방법은 LLM agent를 각 turn마다 하나의 action을 선택하는 단일 시간 척도에서 동작하는 <em>flat</em> policy로 모델링한다. Sparse-reward 설정에서는 이는 agent가 멀리 떨어진 trajectory 종료 신호만으로 장기 의존성을 추론하도록 강제하며, 복잡한 환경에서 비효율적인 학습과 불안정한 행동으로 이어지는 경우가 많다. 우리는 <strong>HiPER</strong>를 제안한다. 이는 LLM agent가 flat RL의 취약한 long-horizon 행동과 sparse outcome feedback 하의 약한 credit assignment를 극복하도록, high-level subgoal planning과 low-level action execution을 공동으로 모델링하고 최적화하는 새로운 <strong>Hi</strong>erarchical <strong>P</strong>lan-<strong>E</strong>xecute <strong>R</strong>L framework이다. 여러 turn에 걸쳐 지속되는 subgoal을 유지하고 언제 이를 전환할지 명시적으로 결정함으로써, HiPER는 sparse feedback 하에서의 학습을 촉진하는 구조화된 중간 decision point를 도입하고, 암묵적인 multi-turn 구조를 서로 다른 시간 척도에서 학습 가능한 decision으로 변환한다. 효과적인 학습을 위해 우리는 Hierarchical Advantage Estimation(HAE)을 도입한다. 이는 action execution과 subgoal transition 모두에 credit을 할당하고, flat advantage estimation에 비해 variance reduction을 달성하는 두 시간 척도 policy gradient method이다. 실험적으로 HiPER는 도전적인 interactive benchmark에서 state-of-the-art 성능을 달성하여 ALFWorld에서 97.4\\%의 성공률(기존 최고 방법 대비 +6.6\\%), WebShop에서 83.3\\%를 기록했으며, 특히 여러 종속 subtask를 요구하는 long-horizon 작업에서 큰 향상을 보였다. 이러한 결과는 다중 turn LLM agent의 확장 가능한 RL 학습을 위해 명시적인 hierarchical decomposition이 중요함을 보여 준다.</p>"},{"id":"65777","en":"XRPO: Pushing the Limits of GRPO with Targeted Exploration and Exploitation","ko":"XRPO: 표적 탐색과 활용으로 GRPO의 한계 밀어붙이기","authors":"Udbhav Bamba, Minghao Fang, Yifan Yu, Haizhong Zheng, Fan Lai","pos":"#112","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=AE6U9HvTHc","abs":"<p>Reinforcement learning algorithms such as GRPO have driven recent advances in large language model (LLM) reasoning. While scaling the number of rollouts stabilizes training, existing approaches suffer from limited exploration on challenging prompts and leave informative feedback signals underexploited, due to context-independent rollout allocation across prompts (e.g., generating 16 rollouts per prompt) and relying heavily on sparse rewards. This paper presents XRPO (eXplore–eXploit GRPO), a unified framework that recasts policy optimization through the principled lens of rollout exploration–exploitation. To enhance exploration, XRPO introduces a mathematically grounded rollout allocator that adaptively prioritizes prompts with higher potential for uncertainty reduction. It further addresses stagnation on zero-reward prompts through an in-context seeding strategy that injects curated exemplars, steering the model into more difficult reasoning trajectories. To strengthen exploitation, XRPO develops a group-relative, novelty-aware advantage sharpening mechanism that leverages sequence likelihoods to amplify low-probability yet correct responses, thereby extending the policy’s reach beyond sparse rewards. Experiments across diverse math and coding benchmarks on both reasoning and non-reasoning models demonstrate that XRPO outperforms existing advances (e.g., GRPO and GSPO) up to 4% pass@1 and 6% cons@32, while accelerating training convergence by up to 2.7x.</p>"},{"id":"62398","en":"Advancing LLM Reasoning with Natural Language and Numerical Feedback","ko":"자연어와 수치 Feedback을 활용한 LLM 추론 향상","authors":"Xiaoying Zhang, Yipeng Zhang, Hao Sun, Kaituo Feng, Chaochao Lu, Chao Yang, Helen M Meng","pos":"#114","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=gz7hVnrRWq","abs":"<p>Recent advances in reinforcement learning (RL) using numerical rewards have significantly enhanced the complex reasoning capabilities of large language models (LLMs). However, we identify three fundamental limitations of purely numerical feedback: performance plateaus, ineffective spontaneous self-reflection, and persistent failures. We show that plateaued RL models can successfully refine failed solutions when given natural language critiques. Motivated by this, we propose Critique-GRPO, an online RL framework that integrates both natural language and numerical feedback for policy optimization. This approach enables LLMs to learn simultaneously from initial responses and critique-guided refinements, effectively internalizing the exploration benefits of both stages. Extensive experiments show that Critique-GRPO outperforms all compared supervised and RL-based fine-tuning methods, achieving average Pass@1 improvements of approximately +15.0-21.6% on various Qwen models and +7.3% on Llama-3.2-3B-Instruct across eight challenging reasoning tasks. Notably, Critique-GRPO facilitates effective self-improvement through self-critiquing, achieving substantial gains over GRPO, e.g., a +16.7% Pass@1 improvement on AIME 2024.</p>","absKo":"<p>수치적 reward를 사용하는 reinforcement learning (RL)의 최근 발전은 large language model (LLM)의 복잡한 추론 능력을 크게 향상시켰다. 그러나 우리는 순수한 수치 피드백의 세 가지 근본적 한계를 확인했다. 성능 정체, 비효율적인 자발적 자기성찰, 그리고 지속적인 실패이다. 우리는 plateau 상태의 RL model이 자연어 critique를 제공받으면 실패한 해를 성공적으로 정제할 수 있음을 보인다. 이러한 점에 착안하여, 우리는 natural language와 numerical feedback을 모두 통합하여 policy optimization을 수행하는 online RL framework인 Critique-GRPO를 제안한다. 이 접근법은 LLM이 초기 응답과 critique-guided refinement로부터 동시에 학습할 수 있게 하며, 두 단계의 exploration 이점을 효과적으로 내재화한다. 광범위한 실험은 Critique-GRPO가 비교 대상인 모든 supervised 및 RL 기반 fine-tuning 방법을 능가함을 보여주며, 다양한 Qwen model에서 평균 Pass@1을 약 +15.0-21.6% 향상시키고, 8개의 까다로운 추론 task에서 Llama-3.2-3B-Instruct에 대해 +7.3% 향상시킨다. 특히 Critique-GRPO는 self-critiquing을 통한 효과적인 self-improvement를 가능하게 하며, 예를 들어 AIME 2024에서 Pass@1을 +16.7% 향상시키는 등 GRPO 대비 상당한 개선을 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"64499","en":"MEAL: A Benchmark for Continual Multi-Agent Reinforcement Learning","ko":"MEAL: 지속적 다중 에이전트 강화학습을 위한 벤치마크","authors":"Tristan Tomilin, Luka van den Boogaard, Samuel Garcin, Constantin Ruhdorfer, Bram Grooten, Fabrice Kusters, Yali Du, Andreas Bulling, Mykola Pechenizkiy, Meng Fang","pos":"#116","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Mxg6mo1Xzj","abs":"<p>Benchmarks play a central role in reinforcement learning (RL) research, yet their computational constraints often shape what is studied. Despite the motivation of lifelong learning, most continual RL papers consider only 3–10 sequential tasks, as CPU-bound environments make longer sequences impractical. Meanwhile, continual learning in cooperative multi-agent settings remains largely unexplored. To address these gaps, we introduce <strong>MEAL</strong> (<strong>M</strong>ulti-agent <strong>E</strong>nvironments for <strong>A</strong>daptive <strong>L</strong>earning), the first benchmark for continual multi-agent RL. By leveraging JAX and GPU acceleration, MEAL enables training on sequences of 100 tasks on a single GPU in a few hours. We find that long task sequences reveal failure modes that do not appear at smaller scales.</p>","absKo":"<p>Benchmarks는 reinforcement learning (RL) 연구에서 중심적인 역할을 하지만, 그 computational 제약은 종종 무엇이 연구되는지를 좌우한다. lifelong learning의 동기에도 불구하고, 대부분의 continual RL 논문은 CPU-bound 환경 때문에 더 긴 sequence가 비현실적이라는 이유로 3–10개의 sequential task만을 다룬다. 한편, cooperative multi-agent setting에서의 continual learning은 여전히 거의 탐구되지 않았다. 이러한 공백을 메우기 위해, 우리는 continual multi-agent RL을 위한 첫 benchmark인 <strong>MEAL</strong> (<strong>M</strong>ulti-agent <strong>E</strong>nvironments for <strong>A</strong>daptive <strong>L</strong>earning)을 소개한다. JAX와 GPU acceleration을 활용함으로써, MEAL은 단일 GPU에서 수 시간 만에 100개 task sequence에 대한 training을 가능하게 한다. 우리는 긴 task sequence가 더 작은 scale에서는 나타나지 않는 failure mode를 드러낸다는 것을 발견했다.</p>"},{"id":"61148","en":"Tvcache: A Tool-Value Cache for Post-Training LLM Agents","ko":"Tvcache: Post-Training LLM Agent를 위한 Tool-Value Cache","authors":"Abhishek Vijaya Kumar, Bhaskar Kataria, Byungsoo Oh, Emaad Manzoor, Rachee Singh","pos":"#118","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=tDft0AHhzH","abs":"<p>In RL post-training of LLM agents, calls to ex ternal tools take several seconds or even min- utes, leaving allocated GPUs idle and inflating post-training time and cost. While many tool invocations repeat across parallel rollouts and could in principle be cached, naively caching their outputs for reuse is incorrect since tool outputs  depend on the environment state induced by prior agent interactions. We present TVCACHE, a stateful tool-value cache for LLM agent post- training. TVCACHE maintains a tree of observed tool-call sequences and performs longest-prefix matching for cache lookups: a hit occurs only when the agent’s full tool history matches a previ- ously executed sequence, guaranteeing identical environment state. On three diverse workloads— terminal-based tasks, SQL generation, and video understanding—TVCACHE achieves cache hit rates of up to 70% and reduces median tool call execution time by up to 6.9×, with no degradation in post-training reward accumulation.</p>","absKo":"<p>LLM agent의 RL post-training에서 외부 tool 호출은 수 초에서 길게는 수 분까지 걸리며, 이로 인해 할당된 GPU가 유휴 상태로 남고 post-training 시간과 비용이 증가한다. 많은 tool invocation은 병렬 rollout 전반에서 반복되며 원칙적으로 캐시할 수 있지만, tool output은 이전 agent interaction에 의해 유도된 environment state에 의존하므로 단순히 출력을 캐시해 재사용하는 것은 올바르지 않다. 우리는 LLM agent post-training을 위한 stateful tool-value cache인 TVCACHE를 제안한다. TVCACHE는 관측된 tool-call sequence의 tree를 유지하고 cache lookup을 위해 longest-prefix matching을 수행한다. 즉, agent의 전체 tool history가 이전에 실행된 sequence와 정확히 일치할 때에만 hit가 발생하므로, 동일한 environment state가 보장된다. terminal 기반 task, SQL generation, video understanding이라는 서로 다른 세 가지 workload에서 TVCACHE는 최대 70%의 cache hit rate를 달성하고 median tool call execution time을 최대 6.9배 줄이면서, post-training reward accumulation의 저하는 발생시키지 않는다.</p>"},{"id":"61677","en":"TreePO: Enhancing Policy Efficacy and Inference Efficiency with Tree Modeling","ko":"TreePO: Tree Modeling으로 Policy 효과성과 Inference 효율 향상","authors":"Yizhi Li, Qingshui Gu, Zhoufutu Wen, Ziniu Li, Ruibin Yuan, Tianshun Xing, Shuyue Guo, Tuney Zheng, 周欣, Xingwei Qu, Wangchunshu Zhou, Zheng Zhang, Wei Shen, Wei Xue, Qian Liu, Chenghua Lin, Jian Yang, Ge Zhang, Wenhao Huang","pos":"#119","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=npsWK8rgYO","abs":"<p>Recent advancements in aligning large language models via reinforcement learning have achieved remarkable gains in solving complex reasoning problems, but at the cost of expensive on-policy rollouts and limited exploration of diverse reasoning paths. In this work, we introduce TreePO, involving a self-guided rollout algorithm that views sequence generation as a tree-structured searching process. Composed of dynamic tree sampling policy and fixed-length segment decoding, TreePO leverages local uncertainty to warrant additional branches. By amortizing computation across common prefixes and pruning low-value paths early, TreePO essentially reduces the per-update compute burden while preserving or enhancing exploration diversity. Key contributions include: (1) a segment-wise sampling algorithm that alleviates the KV cache burden through contiguous segments and spawns new branches along with an early-stop mechanism; (2) a tree-based segment-level advantage estimation that considers both global and local proximal policy optimization. and (3) analysis on the effectiveness of probability and quality-driven dynamic divergence and fallback strategy. We empirically validate the performance gain of \\modelname on a set reasoning benchmarks and the efficiency saving of GPU hours from 22% up to 43% of the sampling design for the trained models, meanwhile showing up to 40% reduction at trajectory-level and 35% at token-level sampling compute for the existing models. While offering a free lunch of inference efficiency, TreePO reveals a practical path toward scaling RL-based post-training with fewer samples and less compute.</p>","absKo":"<p>reinforcement learning을 통한 large language model 정렬의 최근 진전은 복잡한 reasoning problem 해결에서 놀라운 향상을 달성했지만, expensive on-policy rollout과 다양한 reasoning path에 대한 제한된 탐색이라는 대가를 치렀다. 본 연구에서는 sequence generation을 tree-structured searching process로 보는 self-guided rollout algorithm인 TreePO를 소개한다. dynamic tree sampling policy와 fixed-length segment decoding으로 구성된 TreePO는 local uncertainty를 활용하여 추가 branch를 보장한다. 공통 prefix에 걸쳐 계산을 amortize하고 low-value path를 조기에 pruning함으로써, TreePO는 본질적으로 per-update compute burden을 줄이면서도 exploration diversity를 보존하거나 향상시킨다. 핵심 기여는 다음과 같다. (1) 연속된 segment를 통해 KV cache 부담을 완화하고 early-stop mechanism과 함께 새로운 branch를 생성하는 segment-wise sampling algorithm, (2) global 및 local proximal policy optimization을 모두 고려하는 tree-based segment-level advantage estimation, (3) probability 및 quality-driven dynamic divergence와 fallback strategy의 효과에 대한 분석. 우리는 일련의 reasoning benchmark에서 \\modelname의 성능 향상과, 학습된 model에 대한 sampling design에서 GPU hour를 22%에서 최대 43%까지 절감하는 효율 개선을 실증적으로 검증했으며, 동시에 기존 model에 대해 trajectory-level에서 최대 40%, token-level sampling compute에서 35% 감소를 보였다. inference 효율의 free lunch를 제공하는 동시에, TreePO는 더 적은 sample과 더 적은 compute로 RL-based post-training을 확장하는 실용적인 경로를 제시한다.</p>"},{"id":"61374","en":"Population-Free Pareto Tracking for Sample-Efficient Multi-Policy MORL","ko":"Sample-Efficient Multi-Policy MORL을 위한 Population-Free Pareto Tracking","authors":"Zeyu Zhao, Yueling Che, Kaichen Liu, Jian Li, Junmei Yao","pos":"#120","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=qtzu9pGH7S","abs":"<p>Multi-objective reinforcement learning (MORL) is a fundamental framework for real-world decision-making problems involving multiple conflicting criteria. Existing multi-policy (MP) methods typically rely on online evolutionary frameworks that maintain large policy populations, leading to high sample complexity and excessive agent–environment interactions.   To mitigate these limitations, we present Multi-policy Pareto Front Tracking (MPFT), a framework without a self-evolving population. It leverages an efficient Pareto-tracking mechanism initialized with single-objective extreme policies to trace the Pareto front, and further densifies sparse regions to achieve an accurate approximation of the full Pareto front. MPFT can be seamlessly integrated with advanced offline MORL algorithms, thereby substantially improving sample efficiency. We evaluate MPFT on six robotic control tasks with up to three objectives and three high-dimensional tasks with more than three objectives. Experimental results show that MPFT outperforms state-of-the-art baselines in terms of hypervolume and expected utility. It also significantly reduces agent–environment interactions. These results further demonstrate that MPFT serves as a general-purpose framework that can seamlessly integrate both online and offline MORL algorithms.</p>","absKo":"<p>Multi-objective reinforcement learning (MORL)은 여러 상충하는 기준을 포함하는 실제 의사결정 문제를 위한 근본적인 프레임워크다. 기존의 multi-policy (MP) 방법은 일반적으로 큰 policy population을 유지하는 online evolutionary framework에 의존하여, 높은 sample complexity와 과도한 agent–environment interaction을 초래한다. 이러한 한계를 완화하기 위해, 우리는 self-evolving population이 없는 프레임워크인 Multi-policy Pareto Front Tracking (MPFT)를 제안한다. MPFT는 single-objective extreme policy로 초기화된 효율적인 Pareto-tracking 메커니즘을 활용하여 Pareto front를 추적하고, 희소한 구간을 더욱 조밀하게 만들어 전체 Pareto front를 정확하게 근사한다. MPFT는 고급 offline MORL 알고리즘과 매끄럽게 통합될 수 있으며, 이를 통해 sample efficiency를 크게 향상시킨다. 우리는 최대 세 개의 objective를 갖는 여섯 개의 로보틱 제어 task와 세 개 이상의 objective를 갖는 세 개의 고차원 task에서 MPFT를 평가한다. 실험 결과는 MPFT가 hypervolume과 expected utility 측면에서 state-of-the-art baseline을 능가함을 보여준다. 또한 agent–environment interaction을 크게 줄인다. 이러한 결과는 MPFT가 online 및 offline MORL 알고리즘을 모두 매끄럽게 통합할 수 있는 범용 프레임워크로 기능함을 추가로 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"66679","en":"OpenHA: A Series of Open-Source Hierarchical Agentic Models in Minecraft","ko":"OpenHA: Minecraft에서의 오픈소스 계층적 Agentic 모델 시리즈","authors":"Zihao Wang, Muyao Li, Kaichen He, Xiangyu Wang, Zhancun Mu, Minghao Liu, Anji Liu, Yitao Liang","pos":"#121","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=1RQIaGQV8v","abs":"<p>A critical challenge in developing capable AI agents is defining their \"action space''—the set of possible actions they can take. These spaces can range widely, from generating code and using language skills to operating on latent representations or raw joystick controls. Through a large-scale study in Minecraft, we discovered a major dilemma: no single action space is universally best. The most effective action space is highly task-dependent, which complicates the goal of building one generalist agent that can handle everything. To solve this, we introduce Chain-of-Action (CoA), a novel framework that unifies high-level abstracted actions and low-level control actions within a single model. With CoA, an abstract goal is not just a final command; instead, it serves as an intermediate reasoning step that guides the model to generate the precise, executable actions needed to complete the task. Furthermore, we show that an All-in-One generalist agent, trained on a diverse mix of action spaces using CoA, learns a more generalizable policy. This unified agent achieves a new state-of-the-art, outperforming strong, specialized baselines. To support the research community, we are releasing the OpenHA (Open Hierarchical Agents) suite, which includes our benchmark of over 800 tasks, curated datasets, source code, and all model checkpoints at: \\url{https://anonymous.4open.science/anonymize/OpenHA-ACFE}.</p>"},{"id":"65717","en":"Learning What to Generate: A Reinforcement Learning-based Closed-Loop Augmentation Framework for Person Re-identification","ko":"무엇을 생성할지 학습하기: 사람 재식별을 위한 강화학습 기반 폐루프 증강 프레임워크","authors":"Xincheng Shi, Changxiao Ma, Yuzhuo Ma, Yongfei Zhang, Rongye Shi","pos":"#122","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=AtsZrkFBA6","abs":"<p>Person re-identification (ReID) models are sensitive to long-tail nuisances (e.g., rare viewpoints, occlusions, complex backgrounds), yet current generative augmentation is largely open-loop: prompts/conditions are sampled heuristically without verifying whether the synthesized samples improve ReID discriminability. We introduce ReasonAug, a closed-loop framework that learns an image-conditioned instruction policy for a frozen generator, turning augmentation into a sequential decision problem over instruction tokens. A Semantic Reasoning Agent (SRA) performs hierarchical planning from global semantics to identity-critical local cues, producing structured edit instructions whose utility is verified by downstream ReID feedback. To make closed-loop optimization reliable, we propose Metric-Aligned Gated Reward (MAGR), which converts metric-learning objectives into a dense reward while gating task shaping by identity preservation to prevent reward hacking, and Structure-Aware Entropy (SAE), which allocates exploration per token to lock identity-critical cues while diversifying nuisance factors. Experiments on Market-1501 and MSMT17 demonstrate state-of-the-art performance, confirming that closing the augmentation loop and learning what to generate yield more discriminative training data than open-loop alternatives.</p>"},{"id":"66241","en":"DeepHA: Scaling Action Chains Elicits Deep Hierarchical Agents","ko":"DeepHA: 행동 사슬 확장이 심층 계층적 에이전트를 이끌어낸다","authors":"Zihao Wang, Muyao Li, Kaichen He, Haowei Lin, Xiaojian Ma, Anji Liu, Yitao Liang","pos":"#124","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=5W0ezwAurK","abs":"<p>Prevailing autonomous agents are often constrained by a single, predefined action space, which limits their generalization capabilities across diverse tasks and can introduce compounding errors through decoupled policy execution. To address these limitations, we introduce the Deep Hierarchical Agent (DeepHA), a unified architecture that operates across a mixture of heterogeneous action spaces, flexibly generating actions ranging from high-level semantic skills to low-level motor controls. We further propose a Chain-of-Action (CoA) reasoning framework, which enables the agent to use higher-level abstract actions as structured `thoughts' to guide the generation of more granular, subsequent actions. To manage the computational demands of this deep reasoning in long-horizon tasks, we develop a memory-efficient mechanism that dynamically compresses historical context and leverages Key-Value (KV) caching, reducing context length by approximately 75% without sacrificing performance. We conduct extensive evaluations on a new, large-scale benchmark of over 800 diverse Minecraft tasks. Results show that DHA significantly outperforms prior methods, establishing a new state-of-the-art and demonstrating superior generalization, particularly in complex, multi-step planning tasks. Our work presents a novel, unified framework for building more capable and efficient autonomous agents.</p>"},{"id":"62012","en":"Stable Asynchrony: Variance-Controlled Off-Policy RL for LLMs","ko":"Stable Asynchrony: LLM용 variance-controlled off-policy RL","authors":"Luke Huang, Zhuoyang Zhang, Qinghao Hu, Shang Yang, Song Han","pos":"#1708","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=kiC03dyH9P","abs":"<p>Reinforcement learning (RL) is widely used to improve large language models (LLMs) on reasoning tasks, and asynchronous RL training is attractive because it increases end-to-end throughput. However, for widely adopted critic-free policy-gradient methods such as REINFORCE and GRPO, high asynchrony makes the policy-gradient estimator <strong>markedly higher variance</strong>: stale off-policy rollouts induce heavy-tailed importance ratios, causing a small fraction of samples to dominate each update. This amplification makes gradients noisy and learning unstable relative to matched on-policy training. Across math and reasoning benchmarks, we find collapse is preceded by sharp drops in effective sample size (ESS) and unstable gradient norms. Motivated by this diagnosis, we propose <strong>V</strong>ariance <strong>C</strong>ontrolled <strong>P</strong>olicy <strong>O</strong>ptimization (VCPO), a drop-in stabilization method for REINFORCE/GRPO-style algorithms that (i) <strong>rescales learning rate according to effective sample size</strong> to dampen unreliable updates, and (ii) applies a <strong>closed-form minimum-variance baseline</strong> for the off-policy setting, avoiding an auxiliary value model and adding minimal overhead. Empirically, VCPO substantially improves robustness in highly asynchronous regimes across models sizes and tasks, reducing long-context, multi-turn training compute by 1.96×. Overall, our results demonstrate explicitly controlling policy-gradient variance is key to making asynchronous RL reliable at scale.</p>","absKo":"<p>Reinforcement learning(RL)은 reasoning task에서 large language model(LLM)을 향상시키는 데 널리 사용되며, asynchronous RL training은 end-to-end throughput을 높여주기 때문에 매력적이다. 그러나 REINFORCE와 GRPO처럼 널리 쓰이는 critic-free policy-gradient 방법에서는 높은 비동기성이 policy-gradient estimator의 분산을 <strong>현저하게 증가</strong>시킨다. 오래된 off-policy rollout이 heavy-tailed importance ratio를 유발하여, 소수의 샘플이 각 update를 지배하게 되기 때문이다. 이러한 증폭은 gradient를 noisy하게 만들고, matching된 on-policy training에 비해 학습을 불안정하게 만든다. 수학 및 reasoning benchmark 전반에서, collapse는 effective sample size(ESS)의 급격한 하락과 불안정한 gradient norm에 선행된다는 것을 발견했다. 이러한 진단에 근거해, 우리는 REINFORCE/GRPO 스타일 알고리즘을 위한 즉시 적용 가능한 안정화 방법인 <strong>V</strong>ariance <strong>C</strong>ontrolled <strong>P</strong>olicy <strong>O</strong>ptimization(VCPO)을 제안한다. 이 방법은 (i) <strong>effective sample size에 따라 learning rate를 재조정</strong>하여 신뢰할 수 없는 update를 완화하고, (ii) off-policy setting에서 <strong>closed-form minimum-variance baseline</strong>을 적용하여 보조 value model 없이도 최소한의 오버헤드만 추가한다. 실험적으로 VCPO는 다양한 model size와 task에 걸친 매우 비동기적인 regime에서 견고성을 크게 향상시키며, 긴 context의 multi-turn training compute를 1.96배 줄인다. 전반적으로, 우리의 결과는 policy-gradient variance를 명시적으로 제어하는 것이 asynchronous RL을 대규모로 신뢰 가능하게 만드는 핵심임을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"62715","en":"REAL: Regression-Aware Reinforcement Learning for LLM-as-a-Judge","ko":"LLM-as-a-Judge를 위한 Regression-Aware Reinforcement Learning","authors":"Yasi Zhang, Tianyu Chen, Mingyuan Zhou, Oscar Leong, Ying Nian Wu, Michal Lukasik","pos":"#1807","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=dy8ppwIj4o","abs":"<p>Large language models (LLMs) are increasingly deployed as automated evaluators that assign numeric scores to model outputs, a paradigm known as LLM-as-a-Judge. However, standard Reinforcement Learning (RL) methods typically rely on binary rewards (e.g., 0-1 accuracy), thereby ignoring the ordinal structure inherent in regression tasks; for instance, they fail to recognize that predicting 4 is significantly better than predicting 1 when the ground truth is 5. Conversely, existing regression-aware approaches are often confined to Supervised Fine-Tuning (SFT), limiting their ability to explore optimal reasoning paths. To bridge this gap, we propose REAL (Regression-Aware Reinforcement Learning), a principled RL framework designed to optimize regression rewards, and also proven to be optimal for correlation metrics. A key technical challenge is that the regression objective is explicitly policy-dependent, thus invalidating standard policy gradient methods. To address this, we employ the generalized policy gradient estimator, which naturally decomposes optimization into two complementary components: (1) exploration over Chain-of-Thought (CoT) trajectory, and (2) regression-aware prediction refinement of the final score. Extensive experiments across model scales (8B to 32B) demonstrate that REAL consistently outperforms both regression-aware SFT baselines and standard RL methods, exhibiting significantly better generalization on out-of-domain benchmarks. On Qwen3-32B specifically, we achieve gains of +8.40 Pearson and +7.20 Spearman correlation over the SFT baseline, and +18.30/+11.20 over the base model. These findings highlight the critical value of integrating regression objectives into RL exploration for accurate  LLM evaluation.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large language model(LLM)은 점점 더 model output에 수치 점수를 부여하는 자동 평가기로 배치되고 있으며, 이는 LLM-as-a-Judge로 알려진 패러다임이다. 그러나 표준 Reinforcement Learning(RL) 방법은 일반적으로 binary reward(예: 0-1 accuracy)에 의존하므로, regression task에 내재된 ordinal structure를 무시한다. 예를 들어 정답이 5일 때 4를 예측하는 것이 1을 예측하는 것보다 훨씬 낫다는 사실을 인식하지 못한다. 반대로, 기존의 regression-aware 접근법은 대개 Supervised Fine-Tuning(SFT)에 국한되어 있어 최적의 reasoning path를 탐색하는 능력이 제한된다. 이 간극을 메우기 위해, 우리는 regression reward를 최적화하도록 설계되고 correlation metric에서도 최적임이 증명된 원리 기반 RL framework인 REAL(Regression-Aware Reinforcement Learning)을 제안한다. 핵심 기술적 난점은 regression objective가 명시적으로 policy-dependent이므로 표준 policy gradient method가 무력화된다는 점이다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 generalized policy gradient estimator를 사용하며, 이는 최적화를 자연스럽게 두 개의 상보적 구성요소로 분해한다: (1) Chain-of-Thought(CoT) trajectory에 대한 exploration, (2) 최종 score의 regression-aware prediction refinement. 다양한 model scale(8B에서 32B까지)에서의 광범위한 실험은 REAL이 regression-aware SFT baseline과 표준 RL 방법 모두를 일관되게 능가하며, out-of-domain benchmark에서 훨씬 더 우수한 generalization을 보임을 입증한다. 특히 Qwen3-32B에서는 SFT baseline 대비 Pearson +8.40, Spearman +7.20의 향상을, base model 대비 +18.30/+11.20의 향상을 달성했다. 이러한 결과는 정확한 LLM evaluation을 위해 RL exploration에 regression objective를 통합하는 것이 얼마나 중요한지를 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"60864","en":"MemOCR: Layout-Aware Visual Memory for Efficient Long-Horizon Reasoning","ko":"MemOCR: 효율적인 Long-Horizon Reasoning을 위한 Layout-Aware Visual Memory","authors":"Yaorui Shi, Shugui Liu, Yu Yang, Wenyu Mao, Yuxin Chen, Qi GU, Hui Su, Xunliang Cai, Xiang Wang, An Zhang","pos":"#210","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=vv4TMkyfWA","abs":"<p>Long-horizon agentic reasoning necessitates effectively compressing growing interaction histories into a limited context window. Most existing memory systems serialize history as text, where token-level cost is uniform and scales linearly with length, often spending scarce budget on low-value details. To this end, we introduce <strong>MemOCR</strong>, a multimodal memory agent that improves long-horizon reasoning under tight context budgets by allocating memory space with adaptive information density through visual layout. Concretely, MemOCR maintains a structured rich-text memory (e.g., headings, highlights) and renders it into an image that the agent consults for memory access, visually prioritizing crucial evidence while aggressively compressing auxiliary details. To ensure robustness across varying memory budgets, we train MemOCR with reinforcement learning under budget-aware objectives that expose the agent to diverse compression levels. Across long-context multi-hop and single-hop question-answering benchmarks, MemOCR outperforms strong text-based baselines and achieves more effective context utilization under extreme budgets.</p>","absKo":"<p>Long-horizon agentic reasoning은 증가하는 interaction history를 제한된 context window 안에 효과적으로 압축해야 한다. 기존 memory system의 대부분은 history를 text로 직렬화하며, token-level cost는 균일하고 길이에 따라 선형적으로 증가하기 때문에, 종종 낮은 가치의 세부사항에 희소한 budget을 낭비한다. 이를 위해 우리는 시각적 layout을 통해 adaptive information density로 memory space를 할당함으로써 tight context budget 하에서 long-horizon reasoning을 향상시키는 multimodal memory agent인 <strong>MemOCR</strong>을 제안한다. 구체적으로, MemOCR은 구조화된 rich-text memory(예: heading, highlight)를 유지한 뒤 이를 agent가 memory access를 위해 참조하는 image로 렌더링하여, 중요한 evidence를 시각적으로 우선시하는 동시에 보조 세부사항은 적극적으로 압축한다. 다양한 memory budget에 걸친 견고성을 확보하기 위해, 우리는 budget-aware objective 하에서 reinforcement learning으로 MemOCR을 학습시켜 agent가 다양한 compression level에 노출되도록 한다. long-context multi-hop 및 single-hop question-answering benchmark 전반에서 MemOCR은 강력한 text-based baseline을 능가하며, 극단적인 budget 조건에서도 더 효과적인 context utilization을 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"63942","en":"DADP: Domain Adaptive Diffusion Policy","ko":"DADP: 도메인 적응 Diffusion Policy","authors":"Pengcheng Wang, Qinghang Liu, Haotian Lin, Yiheng Li, Guojian Zhan, Masayoshi Tomizuka, Yixiao Wang","pos":"#211","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=SM1KZV8lLP","abs":"<p>Learning domain adaptive policies that can generalize to unseen transition dynamics, remains a fundamental challenge in learning-based control. Substantial progress has been made through domain representation learning to capture domain-specific information, thus enabling domain-aware decision making. We analyze the process of learning domain representations through dynamical prediction and find that selecting contexts adjacent to the current step causes the learned representations to entangle static domain information with varying dynamical properties. Such mixture can confuse the conditioned policy, thereby constraining zero-shot adaptation. To tackle the challenge, we propose DADP (Domain Adaptive Diffusion Policy), which achieves robust adaptation through unsupervised disentanglement and domain-aware diffusion injection. First, we introduce Lagged Context Dynamical Prediction, a strategy that conditions future state estimation on a historical offset context; by increasing this temporal gap, we unsupervisedly disentangle static domain representations by filtering out transient properties. Second, we integrate the learned domain representations directly into the generative process by biasing the prior distribution and reformulating the diffusion target. Extensive experiments on challenging benchmarks across locomotion and manipulation demonstrate the superior performance, and the generalizability of DADP over prior methods.  More visualization results are available on the https://anonymous.4open.science/w/dadp-webpage-D841.</p>","absKo":"<p>알려지지 않은 transition dynamics에도 일반화할 수 있는 domain adaptive policy를 학습하는 것은 learning-based control에서 여전히 근본적인 과제다. Domain-specific 정보를 포착하기 위한 domain representation learning을 통해 상당한 진전이 이루어졌고, 그 결과 domain-aware decision making이 가능해졌다. 우리는 dynamical prediction을 통해 domain representation을 학습하는 과정을 분석하고, 현재 시점에 인접한 context를 선택하면 학습된 representation이 정적인 domain 정보와 변하는 dynamical property를 서로 얽히게 만든다는 사실을 발견했다. 이러한 혼합은 conditioned policy를 혼란스럽게 하여 zero-shot adaptation을 제한할 수 있다. 이 과제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 unsupervised disentanglement와 domain-aware diffusion injection을 통해 강건한 적응을 달성하는 DADP (Domain Adaptive Diffusion Policy)를 제안한다. 먼저, 우리는 Lagged Context Dynamical Prediction을 도입한다. 이는 future state estimation을 historical offset context에 조건화하는 전략으로, 이 시간적 간격을 늘림으로써 일시적인 성질을 걸러내어 정적인 domain representation을 비지도 방식으로 disentangle한다. 둘째, 우리는 prior distribution을 bias하고 diffusion target을 재정식화함으로써 학습된 domain representation을 생성 과정에 직접 통합한다. locomotion과 manipulation 전반의 까다로운 benchmark에서 수행한 광범위한 실험은 prior method보다 DADP의 우수한 성능과 일반화 가능성을 입증한다. 더 많은 visualization 결과는 https://anonymous.4open.science/w/dadp-webpage-D841 에서 확인할 수 있다.</p>"},{"id":"60620","en":"D-ARL: A Distribution-Matched Asynchronous Reinforcement Learning Framework for Language Reasoning","ko":"D-ARL: 언어 추론을 위한 분포 매칭 비동기 강화학습 프레임워크","authors":"白 寅岐, Xialiang Tong, Jie Wang, Hongyu Liu, Longdi Pan, Jiashuo Li, Zehao Wang, Jianye Hao, Mingxuan Yuan, Feng Wu","pos":"#2111","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=yRbIv7Zd4q","abs":"Asynchronous reinforcement learning (RL) has shown notable success in accelerating the post-training of large language models (LLMs). However, its decoupled data generation and training paradigm introduces a fundamental distributional mismatch between data generated by stale behavior policies and current policy, leading to unstable training and degraded performance. To address this challenge, we propose D-ARL, a **D**istribution-matched **A**synchronous **R**einforcement **L**earning framework that selects high-quality asynchronous samples whose distributions are well aligned with the current policy for policy optimization. Specifically, D-ARL maintains a replay buffer that collects samples from the most recent $K$ behavior policies and proposes a variance-guided metric to select distribution-matched data. During training, D-ARL introduces a multi-behavior policy optimization algorithm to leverage the multi-source nature of the selected samples for policy update. Experiments on six widely used reasoning benchmarks show that D-ARL outperforms state-of-the-art asynchronous methods, achieving an average improvement of 6.4\\% in reasoning performance and 34.7\\% in sample efficiency.","absKo":"비동기 reinforcement learning (RL)은 large language model (LLM)의 post-training을 가속하는 데서 주목할 만한 성과를 보여 왔다. 그러나 데이터 생성과 학습을 분리한 패러다임은 오래된 behavior policy에서 생성된 데이터와 현재 policy 사이에 근본적인 distribution mismatch를 유발하여, 불안정한 학습과 성능 저하로 이어진다. 이 문제를 해결하기 위해 우리는 policy optimization을 위해 현재 policy와 분포가 잘 정렬된 고품질 비동기 sample을 선택하는 **D**istribution-matched **A**synchronous **R**einforcement **L**earning framework인 D-ARL을 제안한다. 구체적으로 D-ARL은 가장 최근 $K$개의 behavior policy에서 sample을 수집하는 replay buffer를 유지하고, distribution-matched data를 선택하기 위해 variance-guided metric을 제안한다. 학습 중에는 D-ARL이 multi-source 특성을 지닌 선택된 sample을 policy update에 활용할 수 있도록 multi-behavior policy optimization algorithm을 도입한다. 널리 사용되는 6개의 reasoning benchmark에서 수행한 실험은 D-ARL이 최첨단 비동기 방법들을 능가하며, reasoning 성능은 평균 6.4\\%, sample efficiency는 34.7\\% 향상됨을 보여준다."},{"id":"63739","en":"Beyond Normalization: Rethinking the Partition Function as a Difficulty Scheduler for RLVR","ko":"Normalization을 넘어서: RLVR을 위한 난이도 스케줄러로서 Partition Function 재해석","authors":"Dohyung Kim, Minbeom Kim, Jeonghye Kim, Lee Sangmook, Sojeong Rhee, Kyomin Jung","pos":"#212","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=U93dBehANs","abs":"<p>Reward-maximizing RL methods enhance the reasoning performance of LLMs, but often reduce the diversity among outputs. Recent works address this issue by adopting GFlowNets, training LLMs to match a target distribution while jointly learning its partition function.  In contrast to prior works that treat this partition function solely as a normalizer, we reinterpret it as a per-prompt expected-reward (i.e., online accuracy) signal, leveraging this unused information to improve sample efficiency. Specifically, we first establish a theoretical relationship between the partition function and per-prompt accuracy estimates. Building on this key insight, we propose \\textbf{Pa}rtition Fun\\textbf{c}tion-Guid\\textbf{ed} \\textbf{RL} (PACED-RL), a  post-training framework that leverages accuracy estimates to prioritize informative question prompts during training, and further improves sample efficiency through an accuracy estimate error–prioritized replay. Crucially, both components reuse information already produced during GFlowNet training, effectively amortizing the compute overhead into the existing optimization process. Extensive experiments across diverse benchmarks demonstrate strong performance improvements over GRPO and prior GFlowNet approaches, highlighting PACED-RL as a promising direction for a more sample efficient distribution-matching training for LLMs.</p>","absKo":"Reward-maximizing RL 방법은 LLM의 reasoning 성능을 향상시키지만, 종종 출력 간 다양성을 감소시킨다. 최근 연구는 이 문제를 해결하기 위해 GFlowNet을 채택하여, partition function을 함께 학습하면서 LLM이 목표 분포를 맞추도록 훈련한다. 기존 연구가 이 partition function을 단순한 normalizer로만 취급한 것과 달리, 우리는 이를 prompt별 expected-reward, 즉 online accuracy signal로 재해석하고, 이 사용되지 않던 정보를 활용해 sample efficiency를 개선한다. 구체적으로, 우리는 먼저 partition function과 prompt별 accuracy estimate 사이의 이론적 관계를 확립한다. 이 핵심 통찰을 바탕으로, 우리는 **Pa**rtition Fun\\textbf{c}tion-Guid\\textbf{ed} \\textbf{RL} (PACED-RL)을 제안한다. 이는 accuracy estimate를 활용하여 학습 중 정보성이 높은 question prompt를 우선순위화하는 post-training framework이며, accuracy estimate error-prioritized replay를 통해 sample efficiency를 추가로 향상시킨다. 핵심적으로, 두 구성 요소 모두 GFlowNet 학습 중 이미 생성된 정보를 재사용하여, 계산 오버헤드를 기존 최적화 과정에 효과적으로 amortize한다. 다양한 benchmark에서의 광범위한 실험은 GRPO와 기존 GFlowNet 접근법보다 강한 성능 향상을 보여주며, PACED-RL이 LLM을 위한 더 sample-efficient한 distribution-matching training의 유망한 방향임을 강조한다.</p>"},{"id":"60543","en":"Beyond Trajectory-Level Attribution: Graph-Based Credit Assignment for Agentic Reinforcement Learning","ko":"궤적 수준 귀인을 넘어: 에이전트형 강화학습을 위한 그래프 기반 크레딧 할당","authors":"Xin Cheng, Shuo He, Lang Feng, Haiyang Xu, Ming Yan, Lei Feng, Bo An","pos":"#213","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=zAFrIOeTCp","abs":"<p>Group-based reinforcement learning (RL) methods have achieved remarkable success in improving the performance of large language models (LLMs) and have been rapidly extended to agentic tasks. However, their credit assignment relies heavily on coarse-grained trajectory-level attribution according to final outcomes, making it difficult to capture the contribution of individual steps, such as valuable steps obscured within failed trajectories. To uncover latent information and enable more faithful step-level credit assignment, we propose Graph-based Group Policy Optimization (GraphGPO), which first aggregates all rollout trajectories into a unified state-transition graph and then estimates the distance from each state to the task goal using the global information encoded in the graph. Finally, GraphGPO assigns credit to each edge by estimating a graph-based advantage, based on how much the transition reduces the distance to the task goal. In this way, GraphGPO significantly improves training efficiency and achieves state-of-the-art performance across a range of challenging benchmarks.</p>","absKo":"<p>Group-based reinforcement learning (RL) method는 large language model (LLM)의 성능 향상에 놀라운 성공을 거두었고, agentic task로 빠르게 확장되고 있다. 그러나 이들의 credit assignment는 최종 결과에 따른 거친 trajectory-level attribution에 크게 의존하므로, 실패한 trajectory 안에 가려진 유용한 step처럼 개별 step의 기여를 포착하기 어렵다. 잠재된 정보를 드러내고 보다 충실한 step-level credit assignment를 가능하게 하기 위해, 우리는 Graph-based Group Policy Optimization (GraphGPO)를 제안한다. GraphGPO는 먼저 모든 rollout trajectory를 하나의 통합된 state-transition graph로 집계한 뒤, graph에 인코딩된 global information을 사용해 각 state에서 task goal까지의 거리를 추정한다. 마지막으로 GraphGPO는 전이가 task goal까지의 거리를 얼마나 줄이는지에 기반한 graph-based advantage를 추정하여 각 edge에 credit을 할당한다. 이러한 방식으로 GraphGPO는 training efficiency를 크게 향상시키며, 다양한 challenging benchmark에서 state-of-the-art performance를 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"60940","en":"Investigating Memory in RL with POPGym Arcade","ko":"POPGym Arcade로 RL의 Memory 조사하기","authors":"Zekang Wang, Zhe He, Borong Zhang, Edan Toledo, Steven Morad","pos":"#215","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=vBMdonzFEV","abs":"<p>How should we analyze memory in deep RL? We introduce tools for analyzing policies under partial observability and revealing how agents use memory to make decisions. To utilize these tools, we present POPGym Arcade, a collection of Atari-inspired, hardware-accelerated environments sharing a single observation and action space. Each environment provides fully and partially observable variants, enabling counterfactual studies on observability. We find that controlled studies are necessary for fair comparisons and identify a pathology where value functions smear credit over irrelevant history. Using this pathology, we demonstrate how out-of-distribution scenarios can contaminate memory, perturbing the policy far into the future.</p>","absKo":"<p>deep RL에서 memory를 어떻게 분석해야 할까? 우리는 partial observability 하의 policy를 분석하고, agent가 decision을 내릴 때 memory를 어떻게 사용하는지 드러내는 도구를 소개한다. 이러한 도구를 활용하기 위해, 우리는 단일 observation space와 action space를 공유하는 Atari-inspired, hardware-accelerated environment 모음인 POPGym Arcade를 제시한다. 각 environment는 fully observable 버전과 partially observable 버전을 모두 제공하여 observability에 대한 counterfactual study를 가능하게 한다. 우리는 공정한 비교를 위해 통제된 연구가 필요하다는 사실을 발견했으며, value function이 무관한 history에 credit을 번지게 하는 pathology를 식별했다. 이 pathology를 통해, out-of-distribution scenario가 memory를 오염시켜 policy를 훨씬 먼 미래까지 교란할 수 있음을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"63464","en":"Reparameterization Flow Policy Optimization","ko":"재파라미터화 Flow 정책 최적화","authors":"Hai Zhong, Zhuoran Li, Xun Wang, Longbo Huang","pos":"#217","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Wx5XHJoeyn","abs":"Reparameterization Policy Gradient (RPG) has emerged as a powerful paradigm for model-based reinforcement learning, enabling high sample efficiency by backpropagating gradients through differentiable dynamics. However, prior RPG approaches have been predominantly restricted to Gaussian policies, limiting their performance and failing to leverage recent advances in generative models. In this work, we identify that flow policies, which generate actions via differentiable ODE integration, naturally align with the RPG framework, a connection not established in prior work. Yet, naively realizing this synergy is non-trivial: it often suffers from training instability and a lack of exploration. We propose Reparameterization Flow Policy Optimization (RFO). RFO computes policy gradients by backpropagating jointly through the flow generation process and system dynamics, unlocking high sample efficiency without requiring intractable log-likelihood calculations. RFO includes two tailored regularization terms for stability and exploration. We also propose a variant of RFO with action chunking. Extensive experiments on diverse locomotion and manipulation tasks—involving both rigid and soft bodies with state or visual inputs—demonstrate the effectiveness of RFO. Notably, on a challenging locomotion task controlling a soft-body quadruped, RFO achieves almost $2\\times$ the reward of the state-of-the-art baseline.","absKo":"Reparameterization Policy Gradient (RPG)는 미분 가능한 dynamics를 통해 gradient를 backpropagation함으로써 높은 sample efficiency를 가능하게 하는, model-based reinforcement learning을 위한 강력한 패러다임으로 부상했다. 그러나 기존 RPG 접근법은 주로 Gaussian policy에 제한되어 성능이 제약되었고, 최근의 generative model 발전을 활용하지 못했다. 본 연구에서는 differentiable ODE integration을 통해 action을 생성하는 flow policy가 RPG framework와 자연스럽게 정렬된다는 점을 밝혀냈으며, 이는 선행 연구에서 확립되지 않았던 연결이다. 그러나 이러한 시너지를 단순하게 구현하는 것은 만만치 않다. 훈련 불안정성과 탐색 부족 문제가 자주 발생하기 때문이다. 우리는 Reparameterization Flow Policy Optimization (RFO)를 제안한다. RFO는 flow generation process와 system dynamics를 함께 backpropagation하여 policy gradient를 계산함으로써, 계산 불가능한 log-likelihood 계산 없이도 높은 sample efficiency를 가능하게 한다. RFO는 안정성과 탐색을 위한 두 개의 맞춤형 regularization term을 포함한다. 또한 action chunking을 적용한 RFO 변형도 제안한다. 상태 또는 visual input을 사용하는 강체 및 연체 시스템을 포함한 다양한 locomotion 및 manipulation task에서의 광범위한 실험은 RFO의 효과를 입증한다. 특히 연체 quadruped를 제어하는 까다로운 locomotion task에서 RFO는 state-of-the-art baseline의 보상 대비 거의 $2\\times$를 달성한다."},{"id":"63834","en":"Temporal Difference Calibration in Sequential Tasks: Application to Vision-Language-Action Models","ko":"순차 작업에서의 temporal difference calibration: vision-language-action 모델 적용","authors":"Shelly Francis-Meretzki, Mirco Mutti, Yaniv Romano, Aviv Tamar","pos":"#306","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=TIru4KuhcB","abs":"<p>Recent advances in vision-language-action (VLA) models for robotics have highlighted the importance of reliable uncertainty quantification in sequential tasks. However, assessing and improving calibration in such settings remains mostly unexplored, especially when only partial trajectories are observed. In this work, we formulate <em>sequential calibration</em> for episodic tasks, where task-success confidence is produced along an episode, while success is determined at the end of it. We introduce a sequential extension of the Brier score and show that, for binary outcomes, its risk minimizer coincides with the VLA policy’s value function. This connection bridges uncertainty calibration and reinforcement learning, enabling the use of temporal-difference (TD) value estimation as a principled calibration mechanism over time.  We empirically show that TD calibration improves performance relative to the state-of-the-art on simulated and real-robot data. Interestingly, we show that when calibrated using TD, the VLA's single-step action probabilities can yield competitive uncertainty estimates, in contrast to recent findings that employed different calibration techniques.</p>","absKo":"<p>로봇을 위한 vision-language-action (VLA) model의 최근 발전은 sequential task에서 신뢰할 수 있는 uncertainty quantification의 중요성을 부각시켰다. 그러나 이러한 setting에서 calibration을 평가하고 개선하는 문제는 여전히 충분히 탐구되지 않았으며, 특히 partial trajectory만 관찰되는 경우에는 더욱 그렇다. 본 연구에서는 episodic task를 위한 <em>sequential calibration</em>을 정식화한다. 여기서 task-success confidence는 episode 진행 중에 생성되지만, 성공 여부는 episode 종료 시점에 결정된다. 우리는 Brier score의 sequential extension을 도입하고, binary outcome의 경우 그 risk minimizer가 VLA policy의 value function과 일치함을 보인다. 이 연결은 uncertainty calibration과 reinforcement learning을 이어주며, temporal-difference (TD) value estimation을 시간에 따른 원칙적 calibration mechanism으로 사용할 수 있게 한다. 우리는 TD calibration이 simulated 및 real-robot data에서 state-of-the-art 대비 성능을 향상시킴을 실증적으로 보인다. 흥미롭게도, TD로 calibration할 경우 VLA의 single-step action probability만으로도 최근의 다른 calibration technique을 사용한 결과와 달리 경쟁력 있는 uncertainty estimate를 얻을 수 있음을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"64209","en":"Learning Task-Sufficient World Models by Synergizing Agentic Exploration and Structured Modeling","ko":"에이전트적 탐색과 구조화된 모델링의 시너지를 통한 과제 충분 세계 모델 학습","authors":"Fan Feng, Yujia Zheng, Minghao Fu, Yongqiang Chen, Guangyi Chen, Kevin Murphy, Biwei Huang, Kun Zhang","pos":"#4016","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=PxpGOLlo02","abs":"<p>Learning and planning in imagination using world models provides an effective paradigm for training agents for decision-making. However, existing approaches often rely on high-dimensional latent spaces or generic visual embeddings that retain many factors irrelevant to control, limiting efficiency and generalization across tasks.  To this end, we study how agents can learn world models with representations that are task-specific, minimal, and sufficient for decision making. We achieve this via a closed-loop synergy between the agent and the world model, in which structured world-model learning distills task-sufficient representations from informative interaction data. On the agent side, agents perform active probing of the environment to collect informative trajectories that expose task-relevant latent factors, guided by an adaptive curriculum. On the world-model side, we learn structured representations over observations to distill compact, task-sufficient latent states from the collected interaction data. This synergy enables the recovery of task-sufficient latent representations that capture all control-relevant factors empirically. Leveraging these representations, the resulting policies achieve improved sample efficiency and systematic generalization, including generalization across skills, object–skill compositions, and previously unseen tasks on standard continuous control and robotic manipulation benchmarks.</p>","absKo":"<p>world model을 이용한 상상 속 학습과 계획은 의사결정을 위한 agent를 훈련하는 효과적인 paradigm을 제공한다. 그러나 기존 접근은 종종 제어와 무관한 많은 요인을 보존하는 고차원 latent space나 일반적인 visual embedding에 의존하여, 효율성과 task 전반의 generalization을 제한한다. 이를 위해 우리는 agent가 decision making에 대해 task-specific하고 minimal하며 sufficient한 representation을 갖는 world model을 어떻게 학습할 수 있는지 연구한다. 우리는 agent와 world model 사이의 closed-loop synergy를 통해 이를 달성하며, 여기서 structured world-model learning은 정보가 풍부한 interaction data로부터 task-sufficient representation을 증류한다. agent 측면에서 agent는 adaptive curriculum의 지도를 받아 환경을 적극적으로 probing하여 task 관련 latent factor를 드러내는 informative trajectory를 수집한다. world-model 측면에서는 관측치에 대한 structured representation을 학습하여 수집된 interaction data로부터 compact하고 task-sufficient한 latent state를 증류한다. 이러한 synergy는 실증적으로 모든 control 관련 요인을 포착하는 task-sufficient latent representation의 복원을 가능하게 한다. 이 representation을 활용하면, 결과 policy는 standard continuous control 및 robotic manipulation benchmark에서 skill 간, object-skill composition 간, 그리고 이전에 보지 못한 task 전반에 걸쳐 향상된 sample efficiency와 체계적인 generalization을 달성한다.</p>"},{"id":"66514","en":"Efficient Preference Poisoning Attack on Offline RLHF","ko":"오프라인 RLHF에 대한 효율적 선호 중독 공격","authors":"Chenye Yang, Weiyu Xu, Lifeng Lai","pos":"#4502","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=32XNOcwH1z","abs":"Offline Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback (RLHF) pipelines such as Direct Preference Optimization (DPO) train on a pre-collected preference dataset,  which makes them vulnerable to preference poisoning attack.  We study label flip attacks against log-linear DPO.  We first illustrate that flipping one preference label induces a parameter-independent shift in the DPO gradient.  Using this key property, we can then convert the targeted poisoning problem into a structured binary sparse approximation problem.  To solve this problem, we develop two attack methods: Binary-Aware Lattice Attack (BAL-A) and Binary Matching Pursuit Attack (BMP-A). BAL-A embeds the binary flip selection problem into a binary-aware lattice and applies Lenstra-Lenstra-Lovász reduction and Babai's nearest plane algorithm;  we provide sufficient conditions that enforce binary coefficients and recover the minimum-flip objective. BMP-A adapts binary matching pursuit to our non-normalized gradient dictionary and yields coherence-based recovery guarantees and robustness (impossibility) certificates for $K$-flip budgets. Experiments on synthetic dictionaries and the Stanford Human Preferences dataset validate the theory and highlight how dictionary geometry governs attack success."},{"id":"63649","en":"Strat-Reasoner: Reinforcing Strategic Reasoning of LLMs in Multi-Agent Games","ko":"Strat-Reasoner: 다중 에이전트 게임에서 LLM의 전략적 추론 강화","authors":"Yidong He, Yutao Lai, Pengxu Yang, Jiarui Gan, Jiexin Wang, Yi Cai, Mengchen Zhao","pos":"#706","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=V0eGsz18uZ","abs":"<p>While Large Language Models (LLMs) excel in certain reasoning tasks, they struggle in multi-agent games where the final outcome depends on the joint strategies of all agents. In multi-agent games, the non-stationarity of other agents brings significant challenges on the evaluation of the reasoning process and the credit assignment over multiple reasoning steps. Existing single-agent reinforcement learning (RL) approaches and their multi-agent extensions fail to address these challenges as they do not incorporate other agents in the reasoning process. In this work, we propose Strat-Reasoner, a novel RL-based framework that improves LLMs' strategic reasoning ability in multi-agent games. We introduce a novel recursive reasoning paradigm where an agent's reasoning also integrates other agents' reasoning processes. To provide effective reward signals for the intermediate reasoning sequences, we employ a centralized Chain-of-Thought (CoT) comparison module to evaluate the reasoning quality. Finally, we compute an accurate hybrid advantage and develop a group-relative RL approach to optimize the LLM policy.  Experimental results show that Strat-Reasoner substantially improves strategic abilities of underlying LLMs, achieving 22.1\\% average performance improvements across various multi-agent games. Our code is publicly available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/Strat-Reasoner-3B04.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large Language Models (LLMs)는 특정 reasoning task에서는 뛰어난 성능을 보이지만, 최종 결과가 모든 agent의 joint strategy에 의해 결정되는 multi-agent game에서는 어려움을 겪는다. multi-agent game에서 다른 agent의 non-stationarity는 reasoning process 평가와 여러 reasoning step에 걸친 credit assignment에 큰 도전을 가져온다. 기존의 single-agent reinforcement learning (RL) 접근과 그 multi-agent 확장은 다른 agent를 reasoning process에 포함하지 않기 때문에 이러한 문제를 해결하지 못한다. 본 연구에서는 multi-agent game에서 LLM의 strategic reasoning 능력을 향상시키는 새로운 RL 기반 framework인 Strat-Reasoner를 제안한다. 우리는 agent의 reasoning이 다른 agent의 reasoning process도 통합하는 새로운 recursive reasoning paradigm을 도입한다. 중간 reasoning sequence에 대한 효과적인 reward signal을 제공하기 위해, centralized Chain-of-Thought (CoT) comparison module을 사용해 reasoning quality를 평가한다. 마지막으로, 정확한 hybrid advantage를 계산하고 group-relative RL approach를 개발해 LLM policy를 최적화한다. 실험 결과, Strat-Reasoner는 기반 LLM의 strategic ability를 크게 향상시켜 다양한 multi-agent game에서 평균 22.1\\%의 성능 향상을 달성했다. 코드는 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/Strat-Reasoner-3B04 에 공개되어 있다.</p>"},{"id":"62860","en":"Fast Mixing Steady-State Control in Markov Decision Processes","ko":"Markov Decision Process에서 빠른 믹싱 정상상태 제어","authors":"Federico Corso, Marco Mussi, Alberto Maria Metelli","pos":"#4501","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=cTBdiaLjlT","abs":"<p>Stability is a property of fundamental importance in real-world systems. Although it has been widely studied and well understood in <em>control theory</em> (CT) for deterministic systems, it is largely overlooked in stochastic systems such as <em>Markov decision processes</em> (MDPs). In this paper, we aim to translate the steady-state control problem, well established in CT, where the goal is to synthesize a controller with prescribed asymptotic stability properties, into the MDP framework.     To this end, we propose the novel <em>fast-mixing steady-state</em> (FMSS) problem. Given an ergodic MDP and a target steady-state distribution, the objective is to synthesize a Markovian policy that induces this distribution with the fastest possible convergence rate. Addressing this problem requires controlling the spectral properties of the induced <em>Markov chain</em> (MC) transition matrix, which generally leads to non-convex programs. Thus, we derive a tractable surrogate objective that leads to a convex program, whose properties we study in terms of approximation quality, feasibility, and computational complexity.     We then move to the learning setting and propose an \"offline\" sample-based algorithm for FMSS (FMSS-SV), designed for tabular MDPs, in which the environment’s transition model is estimated from data. We quantify the impact of transition model estimation errors on both the objective value and the learned policy, and provide a finite-sample complexity analysis.</p>","absKo":"<p>안정성은 실제 시스템에서 근본적으로 중요한 성질이다. 안정성은 deterministic system에 대한 <em>control theory</em>(CT)에서 널리 연구되고 잘 이해되어 왔지만, <em>Markov decision process</em>(MDP)와 같은 stochastic system에서는 대체로 간과되어 왔다. 본 논문에서는 CT에서 잘 정립된 steady-state control 문제, 즉 지정된 asymptotic stability 성질을 갖는 controller를 합성하는 것을 MDP framework로 옮기는 것을 목표로 한다. 이를 위해 우리는 새로운 <em>fast-mixing steady-state</em>(FMSS) 문제를 제안한다. ergodic MDP와 target steady-state distribution이 주어졌을 때, 목표는 이 distribution을 가능한 가장 빠른 수렴 속도로 유도하는 Markovian policy를 합성하는 것이다. 이 문제를 해결하려면 유도된 <em>Markov chain</em>(MC) transition matrix의 spectral property를 제어해야 하며, 이는 일반적으로 non-convex program으로 이어진다. 따라서 우리는 근사 품질, feasible 여부, 계산 복잡도 측면에서 그 성질을 분석한 뒤, convex program으로 이어지는 tractable한 surrogate objective를 도출한다. 이어서 학습 설정으로 이동하여, 환경의 transition model을 data로부터 추정하는 tabular MDP용 FMSS의 ``offline'' sample-based algorithm(FMSS-SV)을 제안한다. 우리는 transition model 추정 오차가 objective value와 학습된 policy 모두에 미치는 영향을 정량화하고, finite-sample complexity analysis를 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"65462","en":"Proximal Decoding: Provably Reducing Copyright Risk for Any Language Model","ko":"Proximal Decoding: 모든 언어 모델의 저작권 위험을 입증 가능하게 감소시키기","authors":"Jacqueline He, Jonathan Hayase, Scott Yih, Sewoong Oh, Luke Zettlemoyer, Pang Wei Koh","pos":"#3310","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=DRHlbrUrhY","abs":"Modern language models (LMs) tend to memorize portions of their training data and reproduce verbatim spans. When the underlying sources are sensitive or copyright-protected, such reproduction raises issues of consent and compensation for creators and compliance risks for developers.  We propose Proximal Decoding, a plug-and-play inference-time method for suppressing verbatim reproduction: it enables decoding from any risky LM trained on mixed-license data by keeping generation in bounded proximity to a permissively trained safe LM.  Proximal Decoding does so by adaptively allocating a user-chosen information budget over the generation trajectory and enforcing per-step constraints that yield a sequence-level guarantee, enabling a tunable risk–utility trade-off. To make Proximal Decoding practically useful, we introduce a new permissively trained safe model (Comma 1.7B), as well as Proximal$\\_{\\mathrm{Byte}}$, a byte-level variant of our method that enables cross-vocabulary fusion via the ByteSampler (Hayase et al., 2025) framework. We evaluate our methods across six model pairs on long-form evaluations of copyright risk and utility. Proximal and Proximal$\\_{\\mathrm{Byte}}$ define a new Pareto frontier, preserving near-original fluency and factuality while eliminating up to 75\\% of the measurable copying gap (averaged over six copying metrics) between the risky baseline and a safe reference, at a modest inference overhead."},{"id":"62562","en":"Explanations are a Means to an End: A Value of Information Framework for Validating Explanations","ko":"설명은 수단이지 목적이 아니다: 설명 검증을 위한 Value of Information 프레임워크","authors":"Ziyang Guo, Berk Ustun, Jessica Hullman","pos":"#3313","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=fVso2kGVrF","abs":"<p>Explanations of model behavior are commonly evaluated via proxy properties weakly tied to the purposes explanations serve in practice. We contribute a decision theoretic framework that treats explanations as information signals valued by the expected improvement they enable on a specified decision task. This approach yields three distinct estimands: (i) a theoretical benchmark that upper-bounds achievable performance by any agent with the explanation, (ii) a human-complementary value that quantifies the theoretically attainable value that is not already captured by a baseline human decision policy, and (iii) a behavioral value representing the causal effect of providing the explanation to human decision-makers. We instantiate these definitions in a practical validation workflow,  and apply them to assess explanation potential and interpret behavioral effects in human–AI decision support and mechanistic interpretability.</p>","absKo":"<p>모델 행동에 대한 설명은 일반적으로 실제로 설명이 수행하는 목적과는 느슨하게만 연결된 proxy property를 통해 평가된다. 우리는 설명을 특정 decision task에서 기대 성능 향상을 통해 가치를 갖는 information signal로 간주하는 decision theoretic framework를 제안한다. 이 접근법은 세 가지 서로 다른 estimand를 도출한다. (i) 설명을 가진 어떤 agent가 달성할 수 있는 성능의 상한을 주는 theoretical benchmark, (ii) baseline human decision policy가 이미 포착하고 있지 않은 theoretically attainable value를 정량화하는 human-complementary value, (iii) human decision-maker에게 설명을 제공했을 때의 causal effect를 나타내는 behavioral value이다. 우리는 이러한 정의를 실용적인 validation workflow로 구현하고, human-AI decision support와 mechanistic interpretability에서 explanation potential을 평가하고 behavioral effect를 해석하는 데 적용한다.</p>"},{"id":"63414","en":"How RLHF Amplifies Sycophancy","ko":"RLHF는 어떻게 아첨을 증폭하는가","authors":"Itai Shapira, Gerdus Benade, Ariel Procaccia","pos":"#3309","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=XN4pWKtA5h","abs":"<p>Large language models often exhibit increased sycophantic behavior after preference-based post-training, showing a stronger tendency to affirm a user’s stated or implied belief even when this conflicts with factual accuracy or sound judgment. We present a formal analysis of how alignment from human feedback can increase this failure mode by identifying an explicit amplification mechanism that causally links optimization against a learned reward to bias in the human preference data used for alignment. We show that the direction of behavioral drift is determined by a covariance under the base policy between endorsing the belief signal in the prompt and the learned reward, and that the first-order effect reduces to a simple mean-gap condition. We then analyze reward learning from pairwise comparisons under random utility models like Bradley–Terry and characterize when bias in human annotators’ preferences induces this reward gap.  Next, we propose a training-time intervention designed to neutralize the amplification mechanism itself. Among all post-trained policies that prevent sycophantic behavior from increasing, we characterize the unique policy closest in KL divergence to the unconstrained post-trained policy, and derive the corresponding minimal reward correction as a closed-form agreement penalty. Computational experiments find that   reward gaps are common and cause behavioral drift in all the configurations considered.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large language models는 preference-based post-training 이후 종종 sycophantic behavior가 증가하며, 사실적 정확성이나 적절한 판단과 충돌하더라도 사용자가 명시하거나 암시한 믿음을 더 강하게 확인해 주려는 경향을 보인다. 우리는 인간 피드백에 의한 alignment가, 학습된 reward에 대한 optimization을 alignment에 사용된 human preference data의 편향과 인과적으로 연결하는 명시적 amplification mechanism을 식별함으로써 이 failure mode를 어떻게 증가시키는지에 대한 형식적 분석을 제시한다. 우리는 행동 drift의 방향이 base policy 아래에서 prompt의 belief signal을 지지하는 것과 학습된 reward 사이의 covariance에 의해 결정되며, first-order effect는 단순한 mean-gap condition으로 환원됨을 보인다. 이어서 우리는 Bradley–Terry와 같은 random utility model 하에서 pairwise comparison으로부터 reward learning을 분석하고, human annotator의 preference 편향이 언제 이러한 reward gap을 유발하는지 규명한다. 다음으로 우리는 amplification mechanism 자체를 무력화하도록 설계된 training-time intervention을 제안한다. sycophantic behavior의 증가를 방지하는 모든 post-trained policy 중에서, 우리는 unconstrained post-trained policy와 KL divergence가 가장 작은 유일한 policy를 특성화하고, 그에 대응하는 최소 reward correction을 closed-form agreement penalty로 유도한다. 계산 실험은 reward gap이 흔하며, 고려한 모든 설정에서 behavioral drift를 유발함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"65450","en":"ASRU: Activation Steering Meets Reinforcement Unlearning for Multimodal Large Language Models","ko":"ASRU: Multimodal Large Language Model을 위한 활성화 조종과 강화 언러닝의 만남","authors":"Jiahui Guang, Yingjie Zhu, Haiyan Wang, Cuiyun Gao, Jing Li, Di Shao, Zhaoquan Gu","pos":"#3109","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=DXq3HH4S5o","abs":"<p>Multimodal large language models (MLLMs) inevitably memorize sensitive cross-modal information during pretraining, making post-deployment unlearning crucial for safety. Existing methods often evaluate unlearning based on output deviations, neglecting generation quality, which can lead to hallucinations or rigid refusals, compromising usability and safety. We propose Activation Steering Meets Reinforcement Unlearning for Multimodal Large Language Models (ASRU), a novel, controllable multimodal unlearning framework that considers generation quality as a key evaluation metric. ASRU first constructs an initial model exhibiting refusal-style responses via activation redirection. It then reinforces the refusal boundary using a customized reward function, effectively unlearning target knowledge while retaining non-target knowledge. Experimental results show that ASRU preserves model utility while markedly enhancing unlearning (+24.61%) and generation quality (5.8×), achieving strong generalization and an efficient forget–retain trade-off with minimal retained supervision.</p>"},{"id":"66791","en":"Unlearning with Asymmetric Sources: Improved Unlearning-Utility Trade-off with Public Data","ko":"비대칭 소스를 이용한 Unlearning: Public Data를 이용한 Unlearning-Utility 트레이드오프 개선","authors":"Ahmed Mehdi Inane, Vincent Quirion, Gintare Karolina Dziugaite, Ioannis Mitliagkas","pos":"#3110","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=0H7OYNDQS4","abs":"Noise-based certified machine unlearning currently faces a hard ceiling: the noise magnitude required to certify unlearning typically destroys model utility, particularly for large-scale deletion requests. While leveraging public data is a standard technique in differential privacy to relax this tension, its role in unlearning remains unexplored. We address this gap by introducing **Asymmetric Langevin Unlearning (ALU)**, a framework that uses public data to mitigate privacy costs. We prove that public data injection suppresses the unlearning cost by a factor of $O(1/n_{\\mathrm{pub}}^2)$, guaranteeing a strict computational advantage over retraining. This establishes a new control mechanism: practitioners can mitigate the need for high noise—and the associated utility loss—by increasing the volume of public data. Crucially, we analyze the realistic setting of **distribution mismatch**, explicitly characterizing how shifts between public and private sources impact utility. We show that ALU enables \"mass unlearning'' of constant dataset fractions -- a regime where standard symmetric methods become impractical -- while maintaining high utility. Empirical evaluations using variational Rényi divergence and membership inference attacks confirm that ALU effectively thwarts privacy attacks while preserving utility under reasonable distribution shifts."},{"id":"61545","en":"The Hidden Risk: Membership Inference Attacks on Multimodal Federated Learning via Modality Imbalance","ko":"숨겨진 위험: Modality Imbalance를 통한 Multimodal Federated Learning의 Membership Inference Attacks","authors":"Chang Ma, Jun Li, Kang Wei, Yipeng Zhou, Ming Ding, Yiyang Ni","pos":"#3111","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=p3Cgr7EgTZ","abs":"<p>Federated learning (FL) faces significant challenges from modality heterogeneity, which motivates multimodal federated learning (MFL) to leverage complementary modalities across decentralized clients for improved performance.  However, modality imbalance introduces a new attack surface, making MFL more vulnerable to membership inference attacks (MIAs), an issue that remains largely unexplored. In this work, we present the first systematic study of MIAs against MFL and propose a modality-aware attack framework. We show that multimodal models are inherently more susceptible to MIAs due to heterogeneous modality contributions, and existing attacks are suboptimal as they treat multimodal parameters as a whole. By performing MIAs on individual modalities, we find that (i) attacking the dominant modality achieves comparable accuracy with lower overhead, and (ii) different modalities expose distinct membership patterns. To identify members with different patterns, we propose a modality-aware framework that exploits cross-modal performance gaps to adaptively select attack modalities and calibrate inference results. Experiments on three datasets show our approach outperforms baselines across multiple metrics.</p>","absKo":"<p>Federated learning (FL)은 modality heterogeneity로부터 중대한 도전에 직면하며, 이는 분산된 client들 간의 상보적 modality를 활용해 성능을 향상시키기 위한 multimodal federated learning (MFL)을 동기 부여한다. 그러나 modality imbalance는 새로운 attack surface를 도입하여 MFL을 membership inference attacks (MIAs)에 더 취약하게 만들며, 이 문제는 아직까지 충분히 탐구되지 않았다. 본 연구에서는 MFL에 대한 MIA를 최초로 체계적으로 연구하고 modality-aware attack framework를 제안한다. 우리는 multimodal model이 이질적인 modality 기여 때문에 본질적으로 MIA에 더 취약하며, 기존 공격은 multimodal parameter를 하나의 전체로 취급하기 때문에 최적이 아님을 보인다. 개별 modality에 대해 MIA를 수행한 결과, (i) dominant modality를 공격하는 것만으로 더 낮은 overhead에서 유사한 정확도를 달성할 수 있고, (ii) 서로 다른 modality가 서로 구별되는 membership pattern을 드러낸다는 점을 발견했다. 서로 다른 pattern을 가진 member를 식별하기 위해, 우리는 cross-modal performance gap을 활용해 공격 modality를 적응적으로 선택하고 inference result를 보정하는 modality-aware framework를 제안한다. 세 개의 dataset에서 수행한 실험은 우리의 방법이 여러 metric에서 baseline을 능가함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"60494","en":"The Forgetting-Retention Dilemma: Certified Unlearning Theory in Continual Learning","ko":"Forgetting-Retention 딜레마: Continual Learning에서 Certified Unlearning 이론","authors":"Yiting Hu, Lingjie Duan, Qian Zhang","pos":"#3112","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=zlIyJEp9nM","abs":"<p>Machine unlearning aims to eliminate the influence of specific data from trained models to safeguard privacy. However, this presents a significant challenge in the context of continual learning (CL), where models update sequentially on dynamic datasets. A major limitation is that current certified unlearning algorithms fail to account for the complex, cumulative model evolution inherent to CL framework. In this work, we establish the first theoretical foundation bridging CL and machine unlearning. We formulate the CL's unlearning objective as the minimization of post-unlearning excess risk, which decomposes into CL excess risk and unlearning loss, characterizing the fundamental trade-off between preserving historical knowledge and targeted forgetting. Under mild assumptions, we first establish an upper bound for the CL excess risk in non-convex models. We then adapt two certified unlearning approaches, gradient-based and Hessian-based, to the CL framework. Our analysis reveals that while the gradient-based approach is less effective than the Hessian-based method in minimizing unlearning loss, it offers the distinct advantage of nearly zero storage overhead for enabling unlearning. This insight inspire us for a combination strategy to minimize storage costs while maintaining post-unlearning performance. Experimental results further validate our theoretical findings.</p>","absKo":"<p>Machine unlearning은 학습된 모델에서 특정 데이터의 영향을 제거하여 privacy를 보호하는 것을 목표로 한다. 그러나 이는 모델이 동적 데이터셋 위에서 순차적으로 갱신되는 continual learning (CL) 맥락에서 큰 도전 과제를 제시한다. 주요 한계는 현재의 certified unlearning 알고리즘이 CL framework에 내재된 복잡하고 누적적인 모델 진화를 반영하지 못한다는 점이다. 본 연구에서는 CL과 machine unlearning을 연결하는 최초의 이론적 토대를 제시한다. 우리는 CL의 unlearning objective를 post-unlearning excess risk의 최소화로 정식화하고, 이를 CL excess risk와 unlearning loss로 분해하여, 과거 지식 보존과 목표 지향적 망각 사이의 근본적인 trade-off를 특징짓는다. 완화된 가정하에서, 먼저 비볼록 모델에서 CL excess risk의 상한을 도출한다. سپس 우리는 gradient-based와 Hessian-based라는 두 가지 certified unlearning 접근법을 CL framework에 적응시킨다. 우리의 분석은 gradient-based 접근이 unlearning loss 최소화 측면에서는 Hessian-based 방법보다 덜 효과적이지만, unlearning을 가능하게 하면서도 저장 오버헤드가 거의 0에 가깝다는 뚜렷한 장점을 지닌다는 점을 보여준다. 이러한 통찰은 저장 비용을 최소화하면서 post-unlearning 성능을 유지하는 결합 전략으로 이어진다. 실험 결과는 우리의 이론적 발견을 추가로 검증한다.</p>"},{"id":"66390","en":"SlaClip: Gradient Norm Slacks can be Indicator for Adaptive Clipping in DP-SGD","ko":"SlaClip: 그래디언트 노름 여유는 DP-SGD에서 적응적 클리핑의 지표가 될 수 있다","authors":"Shuyan Zou, Shaowei Wang, Zhanxing Zhu, Jin Li, Changyu Dong, Vladimiro Sassone, Han Wu","pos":"#3113","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=48suUeYKdb","abs":"Differentially private stochastic gradient descent (DP-SGD) achieves privacy by clipping per-sample gradients and injecting Gaussian noise, but its utility is highly sensitive to the choice of the clipping threshold $C$. A fixed $C$ often degrades performance and necessitates repeated empirical calibration. Existing adaptive clipping methods either modify the gradient update in vanilla DP-SGD, causing additional tuning or optimization overhead, or introduce separate query mechanisms to monitor gradient statistics. In contrast, we leverage the *slack* information induced by the standard clipping operation, an overlooked signal in prior work, and show that it provides an effective indication for adapting $C$.  In light of this, we propose *SlaClip*, a privacy-preserving adaptive clipping strategy using a post-hoc *Slack Indicator*. Under the same training configuration, both *SlaClip*-DP-SGD and vanilla DP-SGD instantiate the identical Gaussian mechanism, and therefore incur equivalent privacy cost. Moreover, it requires minimal task-specific hyperparameter tuning and exhibits robust performance improvement across diverse datasets and model architectures."},{"id":"65300","en":"Revisiting ML Training under Fully Homomorphic Encryption: Convergence Guarantees, Differential Privacy, and Efficient Algorithms","ko":"완전 동형 암호화 하의 ML 학습 재고: 수렴 보장, Differential Privacy, 효율적 알고리즘","authors":"Yvonne Zhou, Mingyu Liang, Ivan Brugere, Danial Dervovic, Yue Guo, Antigoni Polychroniadou, Min Wu, Dana Dachman-Soled","pos":"#3114","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ExQfs4Agz2","abs":"<p>We present the first theoretical convergence analysis of machine learning training under fully homomorphic encryption (FHE), combined with a differentially private (DP) training algorithm tailored to encrypted computation. Our approach improves computational efficiency over standard differentially private gradient descent (DP-GD) while achieving comparable utility. In particular, we prove convergence of approximate gradient descent using polynomial approximations of activation and loss functions, which are required for FHE compatibility. To preserve privacy in downstream tasks, we integrate differential privacy without relying on costly per-sample gradient clipping, enabling scalable encrypted learning. We also provide data-independent hyperparameter selection and theoretically grounded strategies for polynomial approximation which can be of independent interest. Together, these contributions advance the feasibility of efficient, private, and secure machine learning on sensitive data.</p>"},{"id":"61291","en":"Reverse-Engineering Model Editing on Language Models","ko":"Language Model의 모델 편집 역공학","authors":"Zhiyu Sun, Minrui Luo, Yu Wang, Tianxing He, Zhili Chen","pos":"#3115","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=reBRiuo3nr","abs":"<p>Large language models (LLMs) are pretrained on corpora containing trillions of tokens and, therefore, inevitably memorize sensitive information. Locate-then-edit methods, as a mainstream paradigm of model editing, offer a promising solution by modifying model parameters without retraining. However, in this work, we reveal a critical vulnerability of this paradigm: the parameter updates inadvertently serve as a side channel, enabling attackers to recover the edited data. We propose a two-stage reverse-engineering attack named KSTER (KeySpaceReconsTruction-then-EntropyReduction) that leverages the low-rank structure of these updates. First, we theoretically show that the row space of the update matrix encodes a \"fingerprint\" of the edited subjects, enabling accurate subject recovery via spectral analysis. Second, we introduce an entropy-based prompt recovery attack that reconstructs the semantic context of the edit. Extensive experiments on multiple LLMs demonstrate that our attacks can recover edited data with high success rates. Furthermore, we propose subspace camouflage, a defense strategy that obfuscates the update fingerprint with semantic decoys. This approach effectively mitigates reconstruction risks without compromising editing utility. Our code is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/EditATK-26B6.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large language models (LLMs)는 수조 개의 token을 포함하는 코퍼스로 pretrained 되므로, 민감한 정보를 필연적으로 memorization한다. model editing의 mainstream paradigm인 locate-then-edit method는 재학습 없이 model parameter를 수정함으로써 유망한 해결책을 제공한다. 그러나 본 연구에서는 이 paradigm의 중대한 취약점을 드러낸다. parameter update가 의도치 않게 side channel로 작동하여 공격자가 edited data를 복구할 수 있게 만드는 것이다. 우리는 이러한 update의 low-rank structure를 활용하는 2단계 reverse-engineering attack인 KSTER(KeySpaceReconsTruction-then-EntropyReduction)를 제안한다. 먼저, 우리는 update matrix의 row space가 edited subject의 \"fingerprint\"를 인코딩하며, spectral analysis를 통해 정확한 subject 복구가 가능함을 이론적으로 보인다. 다음으로, edit의 semantic context를 재구성하는 entropy-based prompt recovery attack을 제시한다. 여러 LLM에 대한 광범위한 실험은 우리의 공격이 높은 성공률로 edited data를 복구할 수 있음을 보여준다. 더 나아가, 우리는 update fingerprint를 semantic decoy로 은폐하는 defense strategy인 subspace camouflage를 제안한다. 이 접근은 editing utility를 저해하지 않으면서 reconstruction risk를 효과적으로 완화한다. 코드는 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/EditATK-26B6 에서 확인할 수 있다.</p>"},{"id":"63958","en":"Private Learning with Public Feature Conditioning","ko":"공개 특징 조건화를 이용한 프라이버시 학습","authors":"Shuli Jiang, Walid Krichene, Nicolas Mayoraz","pos":"#3116","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=SDyesowNUa","abs":"We study differentially private (DP) regression in settings where each data sample includes public, non-sensitive features—common in applications like recommendation or advertising systems. While such label DP or DP with semi-sensitive features settings have been primarily explored in the context of classification, effective approaches for regression remain underexplored. We introduce $\\textsf{Cond-DP}$, a conditioned variant of $\\textsf{DPSGD}$ that leverages the structure of public feature matrices to improve optimization under privacy constraints. Motivated by the observation that these public features often exhibit rapidly decaying spectra, $\\textsf{Cond-DP}$ incorporates a data-driven conditioning matrix to reshape the optimization landscape and accelerate convergence. We provide convergence guarantees for convex, strongly convex and non-convex settings, and recover standard $\\textsf{DPSGD}$ as a special case when the conditioning matrix is the identity. We show how to construct an effective conditioning matrix for $\\textsf{Cond-DP}$ directly from public features, enabling faster convergence than $\\textsf{DPSGD}$ in private linear regression, without incurring additional privacy cost. Empirically, $\\textsf{Cond-DP}$ with this conditioning matrix consistently outperforms state-of-the-art baselines across a wide range of datasets and model architectures under label DP, demonstrating strong and robust performance in practice.","absKo":"각 데이터 샘플이 공개된 비민감 feature를 포함하는 설정에서의 differentially private (DP) regression을 연구한다. 이는 recommendation이나 advertising system과 같은 응용에서 흔하다. 이러한 label DP 또는 semi-sensitive feature를 포함한 DP 설정은 주로 classification 맥락에서 탐구되어 왔지만, regression을 위한 효과적인 접근법은 상대적으로 덜 연구되었다. 우리는 privacy constraint 하에서 optimization을 개선하기 위해 public feature matrix의 구조를 활용하는 $\\textsf{DPSGD}$의 conditioned variant인 $\\textsf{Cond-DP}$를 제안한다. 이러한 public feature가 빠르게 감소하는 spectrum을 자주 보인다는 관찰에 착안하여, $\\textsf{Cond-DP}$는 data-driven conditioning matrix를 통합해 optimization landscape를 재형성하고 convergence를 가속한다. 우리는 convex, strongly convex, non-convex 설정에서의 convergence guarantee를 제공하며, conditioning matrix가 identity인 경우 standard $\\textsf{DPSGD}$를 특수한 경우로 회수한다. 또한 public feature로부터 직접 $\\textsf{Cond-DP}$를 위한 효과적인 conditioning matrix를 구성하는 방법을 제시하여, 추가 privacy cost 없이 private linear regression에서 $\\textsf{DPSGD}$보다 더 빠른 convergence를 가능하게 한다. 실증적으로, 이 conditioning matrix를 사용한 $\\textsf{Cond-DP}$는 label DP 하에서 다양한 dataset과 model architecture 전반에 걸쳐 state-of-the-art baseline을 일관되게 능가하며, 실제 환경에서 강력하고 견고한 성능을 보인다."},{"id":"63543","en":"Differentially Private Synthetic Tabular Data via Private Evolution","ko":"사적 진화를 통한 차등 프라이버시 합성 표형 데이터","authors":"Toan Tran, Arturs Backurs, Zinan Lin, Victor Reis, Li Xiong, Sergey Yekhanin","pos":"#3200","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=WB0hLRRlcj","abs":"This paper investigates the problem of generating synthetic tabular data with differential privacy (DP) guarantees, enabling data sharing in sensitive domains. Despite extensive study, state-of-the-art methods often focus on minimizing low-order marginal query errors and overlook the challenges posed by high-order correlations. To address this gap, we extend the Private Evolution (PE) framework, originally developed for DP-compliant image and text synthesis, to tabular data. We introduce Tab-PE -- an algorithm for synthetic tabular data generation under DP constraints. Tab-PE iteratively improves a candidate dataset via an evolutionary process that leverages tabular-specialized operators  to produce variations, privately scores them, and selects the highest-quality samples to retain and propagate. In contrast to the original PE, which relies on large foundation models, Tab-PE employs heuristic operators with significantly lower computational costs, makes PE more practical and scalable for tabular data. Through extensive experiments on real-world and simulation datasets, we demonstrate that Tab-PE substantially outperforms prior baselines on datasets exhibiting high-order correlations. Compared to the best baseline -- AIM, Tab-PE improves classification accuracy by up to 10\\% while running 28$\\times$ faster.","absKo":"이 논문은 differential privacy (DP) 보장을 갖는 synthetic tabular data 생성 문제를 다루며, 민감한 도메인에서의 데이터 공유를 가능하게 한다. 광범위한 연구에도 불구하고, 최신 방법들은 종종 low-order marginal query error 최소화에 집중하고 high-order correlation이 야기하는 도전을 간과한다. 이 공백을 메우기 위해 우리는 DP-compliant image 및 text synthesis를 위해 원래 개발된 Private Evolution (PE) framework를 tabular data로 확장한다. 우리는 DP 제약 하에서 synthetic tabular data를 생성하는 알고리즘인 Tab-PE를 도입한다. Tab-PE는 tabular-specialized operator를 활용하여 variation을 생성하고, 이를 private하게 scoring한 뒤, 가장 높은 품질의 sample을 선택하여 유지하고 전파하는 evolutionary process를 통해 candidate dataset을 반복적으로 개선한다. 대규모 foundation model에 의존하는 원래 PE와 달리, Tab-PE는 계산 비용이 훨씬 낮은 heuristic operator를 사용하여 tabular data에 대해 PE를 더 실용적이고 확장 가능하게 만든다. 실제 데이터와 simulation dataset에 대한 광범위한 실험을 통해 Tab-PE가 high-order correlation을 보이는 dataset에서 기존 baseline을 크게 능가함을 보인다. 가장 강력한 baseline인 AIM과 비교하면, Tab-PE는 classification accuracy를 최대 10\\%까지 향상시키는 동시에 28$\\times$ 더 빠르게 동작한다."},{"id":"64135","en":"Enhancing Membership Inference Attacks on Diffusion Models from a Frequency-Domain Perspective","ko":"주파수 영역 관점에서 Diffusion 모델에 대한 멤버십 추론 공격 강화","authors":"Puwei Lian, Yujun Cai, Songze Li, Bingkun BAO","pos":"#3202","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=QZlNaWuxO6","abs":"<p>Diffusion models have achieved tremendous success in image generation, but they also raise significant concerns regarding privacy and copyright issues. Membership Inference Attacks (MIAs) are designed to ascertain whether specific data were utilized during a model's training phase. As current MIAs for diffusion models typically exploit the model's image prediction ability, we formalize them into a unified general paradigm which computes the membership score for membership identification. Under this paradigm, we empirically find that existing attacks overlook the inherent deficiency in how diffusion models process high-frequency information. Consequently, this deficiency leads to member data with more high-frequency content being misclassified as hold-out data, and hold-out data with less high-frequency content tend to be misclassified as member data. Moreover, we theoretically demonstrate that this deficiency reduces the membership advantage of attacks, thereby interfering with the effective discrimination of member data and hold-out data. Based on this insight, we propose a plug-and-play high-frequency filter module to mitigate the adverse effects of the deficiency, which can be seamlessly integrated into any attacks within the general paradigm without additional time costs. Extensive experiments corroborate that this module significantly improves the performance of baseline attacks across different datasets and models.</p>","absKo":"<p>Diffusion model은 image generation에서 큰 성공을 거두었지만, privacy와 copyright 문제에 대한 심각한 우려도 제기한다. Membership Inference Attack (MIA)은 특정 데이터가 model의 training phase에 사용되었는지 판별하기 위해 설계된다. 현재 diffusion model에 대한 MIA는 대체로 model의 image prediction 능력을 활용하므로, 우리는 이를 membership identification을 위한 membership score를 계산하는 통합된 일반 패러다임으로 정식화한다. 이 패러다임 아래에서, 우리는 기존 attack이 diffusion model이 high-frequency information을 처리하는 방식에 내재한 결함을 간과하고 있음을 실험적으로 발견한다. 그 결과, high-frequency content가 더 많은 member data는 hold-out data로 오분류되고, high-frequency content가 더 적은 hold-out data는 member data로 오분류되는 경향이 있다. 또한 우리는 이 결함이 attack의 membership advantage를 감소시켜 member data와 hold-out data를 효과적으로 구분하는 것을 방해함을 이론적으로 보인다. 이러한 통찰에 기반해, 우리는 결함의 악영향을 완화하는 plug-and-play high-frequency filter module을 제안하며, 추가 시간 비용 없이 일반 패러다임 내의 어떤 attack에도 매끄럽게 통합될 수 있다. 광범위한 실험은 이 module이 다양한 dataset과 model에서 baseline attack의 성능을 크게 향상시킴을 입증한다.</p>"},{"id":"65041","en":"FUSE: Full‑spectrum Unlearnable Examples via Spectral Equalization","ko":"FUSE: Spectral Equalization을 통한 Full-spectrum Unlearnable Example","authors":"Jiale Cai, Gezheng Xu, Zhihao Li, Ruiyi Fang, Ruizhi Pu, di wu, Qicheng Lao, Charles X. Ling, Boyu Wang","pos":"#3203","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=HQhVsrLyv9","abs":"<p>Unlearnable examples (UEs) protect training data by injecting imperceptible perturbations so that models fail to extract exploitable representations. In this paper, we reveal that existing UEs exhibit a critical failure once low-pass filtering is applied, indicating that the effective perturbation signals for unlearnability concentrate predominantly in high frequencies. Hence, we argue that reliable UEs should remain effective across the full spectrum. To this end, we propose <strong>F</strong>ull-spectrum <strong>U</strong>nlearnable Examples via <strong>S</strong>pectral <strong>E</strong>qualization (<strong>FUSE</strong>), which aims to generate spectrum-agnostic perturbations by equalizing the contributions from different bands and enforcing cross-band consistency. Specifically, FUSE adopts a Random Spectral Masking (RSM) strategy during generator training, which randomly removes a contiguous frequency band, forcing the remaining bands to maintain unlearnability. In addition, FUSE further integrates Cross-Band Guidance (CBG), which enforces mutual consistency between high- and low-frequency components, thereby further enhancing low-frequency unlearnability and regulating high-frequency perturbations to preserve the semantic fidelity of images. Extensive experiments across multiple datasets, architectures, and spectral filtering demonstrate the strong protection achieved by FUSE.</p>"},{"id":"65155","en":"Fast and Optimal Algorithms for Private Hypothesis Selection","ko":"Private Hypothesis Selection을 위한 빠르고 최적인 알고리즘","authors":"Hilal Asi, Hongjie Chen","pos":"#3204","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=GFnLVeSyfZ","abs":"<p>We study the problem of private hypothesis selection: given samples from an unknown distribution drawn from a finite hypothesis class, the goal is to identify the best hypothesis under the constraint of differential privacy. Existing algorithms for this problem are either computationally expensive or achieve sub-optimal statistical rates. We propose new algorithms that achieve near-optimal rates while running in nearly linear time in the number of hypotheses. Rather than applying the exponential mechanism directly with a score function that requires pairwise comparisons between hypotheses, our approach introduces a carefully designed loss function based on a small set of strong hypotheses. This structure allows the score to be evaluated efficiently for most hypotheses, yielding significant computational savings. We further extend our algorithms to the agnostic setting, where the true distribution may not belong to the hypothesis class. As an application, we obtain faster differentially private algorithms for universal statistical estimation in low dimensional settings.</p>"},{"id":"60701","en":"Federated Manifold Learning (FML): Tackling Domain Heterogeneity with Structural Knowledge Transfer","ko":"Federated Manifold Learning (FML): Structural Knowledge Transfer로 Domain Heterogeneity 해결하기","authors":"Xutong Mu, Yanbiao Ma, Jia Shi, Xueli Geng, Fengkai Xiang, Tao Zhang, Ke Cheng, Yulong Shen","pos":"#3205","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=xOSfwE4hB3","abs":"<p>Federated Learning (FL) faces significant challenges due to domain heterogeneity, where data from different clients exhibit substantial statistical shifts that hinder the generalization of the global model. Although existing methods attempt to mitigate this by exchanging class prototypes, they fall short by representing an entire class's complex distribution with a single point. This oversimplification disregards the rich structural information within the data, especially across diverse domains. To address this limitation, we propose a paradigm shift from point-based representation to structure-based knowledge transfer. We introduce Federated Manifold Learning (FML), a novel framework that leverages perceptual manifolds—the intrinsic geometric structures of classes in the feature space—as rich knowledge carriers. In FML, clients transmit compressed manifolds, which are adaptively fused on the server using an attention-based Manifold Mutual Learning (MML) mechanism. This process enables domain-specific structures to learn from each other, creating a unified yet flexible global convergence target. Manifold-guided local training, enforced by a manifold approximation loss and a separation loss, further aligns local models with this global structure. Extensive experiments on the Digits and Office31 benchmarks demonstrate that FML substantially outperforms state-of-the-art methods, achieving accuracy improvements of up to 6.48%.</p>","absKo":"Federated Learning (FL)은 domain heterogeneity로 인해 큰 어려움을 겪는다. 서로 다른 client의 데이터는 상당한 통계적 shift를 보이며, 이는 global model의 generalization을 저해한다. 기존 방법들은 class prototype을 교환함으로써 이를 완화하려 하지만, 하나의 class 전체의 복잡한 분포를 단일 점으로 표현한다는 한계를 가진다. 이러한 과도한 단순화는 특히 다양한 domain 전반에 존재하는 풍부한 구조적 정보를 무시한다. 이 한계를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 point-based representation에서 structure-based knowledge transfer로의 paradigm shift를 제안한다. 우리는 perceptual manifold, 즉 feature space에서 class의 본질적 기하학 구조를 풍부한 knowledge carrier로 활용하는 새로운 framework인 Federated Manifold Learning (FML)을 소개한다. FML에서 client는 compressed manifold를 전송하고, 서버는 attention-based Manifold Mutual Learning (MML) mechanism을 사용해 이를 적응적으로 융합한다. 이 과정은 domain-specific structure들이 서로로부터 학습할 수 있게 하여, 통일되어 있으면서도 유연한 global convergence target을 만든다. manifold approximation loss와 separation loss로 강제되는 manifold-guided local training은 local model이 이 global structure에 더 잘 정렬되도록 한다. Digits와 Office31 benchmark에서 수행한 대규모 실험은 FML이 state-of-the-art 방법을 크게 능가하며 최대 6.48%의 정확도 향상을 달성함을 보인다.</p>"},{"id":"64051","en":"Gradient Inversion Attacks Beyond SGD","ko":"SGD를 넘어선 그래디언트 역전 공격","authors":"Guangnian Wan, Gongfan Fang, Xinyin Ma, Xinchao Wang","pos":"#3206","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=RNDJpm1kUW","abs":"<p>Gradient Inversion Attack (GIA) poses a significant threat to federated learning, enabling adversaries to reconstruct private training data from the information shared during training. Prior research has predominantly focused on the vanilla SGD, where the server or an eavesdropper can directly observe true gradients. In practical deployments, however, models may be trained with adaptive optimizers (e.g., Adam, RMSProp, and AdaGrad), for which the observable signal is not raw gradients but momentum-based parameter updates. This setting remains underexplored and undermines traditional gradient-matching strategies, which struggle to recover labels and images from non-gradient updates. To address this gap, this paper explores attacks tailored to modern adaptive optimizers. We present an analytical rule for recovering labels from optimizer updates and propose an update-matching objective that optimizes dummy inputs to reproduce the observed updates. The proposed approach is general and can be directly applied to various optimizers such as Adam, AdaGrad, and RMSProp. Furthermore, we find that, despite being introduced for adaptive optimizers, the proposed objective function also yields stronger attacks in the standard SGD setting. Experiments on datasets such as ImageNet and PACS highlight the effectiveness of our method over existing gradient matching techniques.</p>","absKo":"Gradient Inversion Attack (GIA)는 federated learning에 대한 심각한 위협으로, adversary가 학습 중 공유된 정보를 바탕으로 private training data를 복원할 수 있게 한다. 기존 연구는 주로 vanilla SGD에 집중해 왔으며, 이 경우 server 또는 eavesdropper가 true gradient를 직접 관찰할 수 있다. 그러나 실제 배포 환경에서는 모델이 Adam, RMSProp, AdaGrad와 같은 adaptive optimizer로 학습될 수 있으며, 이때 관찰 가능한 신호는 raw gradient가 아니라 momentum-based parameter update이다. 이 설정은 여전히 충분히 연구되지 않았고, non-gradient update에서 label과 image를 복원하는 데 어려움을 겪는 전통적인 gradient-matching strategy를 약화시킨다. 이러한 공백을 해결하기 위해, 본 논문은 현대적 adaptive optimizer에 맞춘 공격을 탐구한다. 우리는 optimizer update로부터 label을 복원하는 분석적 규칙을 제시하고, 관측된 update를 재현하도록 dummy input을 최적화하는 update-matching objective를 제안한다. 제안 방법은 일반적이며 Adam, AdaGrad, RMSProp과 같은 다양한 optimizer에 직접 적용될 수 있다. 더 나아가, adaptive optimizer를 위해 도입되었음에도 불구하고 제안 objective function이 표준 SGD 설정에서도 더 강력한 공격을 가능하게 함을 발견한다. ImageNet과 PACS 같은 dataset에서의 실험은 기존 gradient matching technique보다 본 방법이 더 효과적임을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"64798","en":"Keeping a Secret Requires a Good Memory: Space Lower-Bounds for Private Algorithms","ko":"비밀을 지키려면 좋은 기억이 필요하다: 프라이빗 알고리즘의 공간 하한","authors":"Alessandro Epasto, Xin Lyu, Pasin Manurangsi","pos":"#3207","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=JiB2eXY8fT","abs":"We study the computational cost of differential privacy in terms of memory efficiency. While the trade-off between accuracy and differential privacy is well-understood, the inherent cost of privacy regarding memory use remains largely unexplored. This paper establishes for the first time an unconditional space lower bound for user-level differential privacy by introducing a novel proof technique based on a multi-player communication game.   Central to our approach, this game formally links the hardness of low-memory private algorithms to the necessity of ``contribution capping''---tracking and limiting the users who disproportionately impact the dataset. We demonstrate that winning this communication game requires transmitting information proportional to the number of over-active users, which translates directly to memory lower bounds.   We apply this framework, as an example, to the fundamental problem of estimating the number of distinct elements in a stream and we prove that any private algorithm requires almost $\\widetilde{\\Omega}(T^{1/3})$ space to achieve certain error rates in a promise variant of the problem. This resolves an open problem in the literature (by Jain et al. and Cummings et al.) and establishes the first exponential separation between the space complexity of private algorithms and their non-private $\\widetilde{O}(1)$ counterparts for a natural statistical estimation task. Furthermore, we show that this communication-theoretic technique generalizes to broad classes of problems, yielding lower bounds for private medians, quantiles, and max-select."},{"id":"62503","en":"LMCleaner: Efficient and Certified Online Unlearning via Influence Propagation Truncation","ko":"LMCleaner: 영향력 전파 절단을 통한 효율적·인증된 온라인 Unlearning","authors":"Jie Xu, Zihan Wu, Wenbo Pan, Jiao Yin, Yong-Feng Ge, Hua Wang, Cong Wang, Xiaohua Jia","pos":"#3208","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=g0Zm1TIrB1","abs":"Existing machine unlearning methods primarily focus on removing data influence after training completes, which is effective for many scenarios, but a complementary capability is needed when removal requests arise during ongoing training. We propose LMCleaner, an efficient and certified \\emph{online} unlearning framework that can process unlearning requests at any training step without waiting for training completion. Our key insight is that influence propagation can be decomposed into a trust region where linear approximation is accurate, and a residual that concentrates in a low-dimensional subspace and can be efficiently masked by calibrated noise. Building on this insight, we design an influence propagation truncation mechanism that treats mini-batch influence as atomic units,  computes influence within a truncation window for efficient removal, and injects subspace-aware noise for certified privacy. Our theoretical analysis proves that the truncation residual decays exponentially with window size and that the unlearned model is $(\\varepsilon, \\delta)$-indistinguishable from retraining. Experiments demonstrate that LMCleaner achieves over $100\\times$ computational savings compared to baselines while maintaining model utility and defending against membership inference attacks.","absKo":"기존 machine unlearning 방법은 주로 학습이 완료된 뒤 데이터의 영향을 제거하는 데 초점을 맞추며, 이는 많은 시나리오에서 효과적이지만, 제거 요청이 학습이 진행 중인 동안 발생할 때는 이를 보완할 수 있는 기능이 필요하다. 우리는 학습 완료를 기다리지 않고 학습의 어느 단계에서든 unlearning 요청을 처리할 수 있는 효율적이고 인증된 \\emph{online} unlearning framework인 LMCleaner를 제안한다. 우리의 핵심 통찰은 influence propagation이 선형 근사가 정확한 trust region과, 저차원 subspace에 집중되어 정교하게 보정된 noise로 효율적으로 마스킹할 수 있는 residual로 분해될 수 있다는 점이다. 이 통찰을 바탕으로 우리는 mini-batch influence를 atomic unit으로 취급하고, 효율적인 제거를 위해 truncation window 내에서 influence를 계산하며, certified privacy를 위해 subspace-aware noise를 주입하는 influence propagation truncation mechanism을 설계한다. 우리의 이론적 분석은 truncation residual이 window 크기에 따라 지수적으로 감소하며, unlearned model이 재학습한 모델과 $(\\varepsilon, \\delta)$-indistinguishable함을 증명한다. 실험은 LMCleaner가 model utility를 유지하고 membership inference attack에 방어하면서 baseline 대비 100배 이상의 계산 절감을 달성함을 보여준다."},{"id":"61306","en":"MINIM: Privacy-Aware Minimal View for Agents via Trusted Local Sanitization","ko":"MINIM: 신뢰 로컬 정제를 통한 Agent용 프라이버시 인식 최소 뷰","authors":"Hexuan Yu, Chaoyu Zhang, Heng Jin, Shanghao Shi, Ning Zhang, Thomas Hou, Wenjing Lou","pos":"#3209","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=rW2xHmYrZA","abs":"<p>Modern LLM-powered autonomous agents increasingly rely on rich user interface (UI) state observations to achieve reliable action grounding in complex digital environments. However, many deployments transmit the full UI state to remote inference servers even when most elements are irrelevant to the current task, which can leak sensitive but unnecessary context such as authentication codes, private notifications, and background application states. We propose MINIM, a trusted local broker that performs privacy-aware minimization on the client side before any observation leaves the device. Grounded in Contextual Integrity (CI), MINIM learns a dual-score representation for each UI element by predicting an inherent sensitivity score (s) and a task-conditioned necessity score (n). These scores drive a trinary disclosure policy that keeps essential elements, abstracts sensitive attributes when needed, and removes task-irrelevant content. We optimize a CI-aware objective that penalizes necessity errors more strongly on high-risk content, enabling aggressive pruning while preserving task-critical information. Experiments on real-world UI observations derived from WebArena show that MINIM reduces task-irrelevant sensitive leakage to 1.1% while preserving 79.8% of task-critical semantic context. Moreover, MINIM retains 95.7% of task-critical interactive affordances, indicating that local sanitization can enforce task-conditioned minimization at both the structural and attribute levels while retaining the signals required for agent actions.</p>","absKo":"<p>Modern LLM-powered autonomous agent는 복잡한 digital environment에서 reliable action grounding을 달성하기 위해 풍부한 user interface (UI) state observation에 increasingly 의존한다. 그러나 많은 배포 환경에서는 현재 task와 무관한 대부분의 element가 존재함에도 불구하고 full UI state를 remote inference server로 전송하며, 이 과정에서 authentication code, private notification, background application state와 같은 민감하지만 불필요한 context가 유출될 수 있다. 우리는 어떤 observation도 device를 떠나기 전에 client side에서 privacy-aware minimization을 수행하는 trusted local broker, MINIM을 제안한다. Contextual Integrity (CI)에 기반하여, MINIM은 각 UI element에 대해 inherent sensitivity score (s)와 task-conditioned necessity score (n)을 예측함으로써 dual-score representation을 학습한다. 이 score는 essential element는 유지하고, 필요할 때 sensitive attribute는 추상화하며, task-irrelevant content는 제거하는 trinary disclosure policy를 구동한다. 우리는 high-risk content에서 necessity error를 더 강하게 패널티하는 CI-aware objective를 최적화하여, task-critical information을 보존하면서도 aggressive pruning이 가능하도록 한다. WebArena에서 파생된 실제 UI observation에 대한 실험은 MINIM이 task-irrelevant sensitive leakage를 1.1%까지 줄이면서 task-critical semantic context의 79.8%를 보존함을 보여준다. 더 나아가 MINIM은 task-critical interactive affordance의 95.7%를 유지하여, local sanitization이 agent action에 필요한 signal을 유지하면서 구조적 수준과 attribute 수준 모두에서 task-conditioned minimization을 강제할 수 있음을 시사한다.</p>"},{"id":"65397","en":"MultiPriv: Benchmarking Individual-Level Privacy Reasoning in Vision-Language Models","ko":"MultiPriv: Vision-Language Model에서 개인 수준 프라이버시 추론 벤치마킹","authors":"Xiongtao Sun, HUI LI, Jiaming Zhang, Yujie Yang, Kaili Liu, Ruxin Feng, Wen Tan, Wei Yang Bryan Lim","pos":"#3210","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=E4CNyyUDSD","abs":"<p>Modern Vision-Language Models (VLMs) pose significant individual-level privacy risks by linking fragmented multimodal data to identifiable individuals through hierarchical chain-of-thought reasoning. However, existing privacy benchmarks remain structurally insufficient for this threat, as they primarily evaluate privacy perception while failing to address the more critical risk of privacy reasoning: a VLM’s ability to infer and link distributed information to construct individual profiles. To address this gap, we propose MultiPriv, the first benchmark designed to systematically evaluate individual-level privacy reasoning in VLMs. We introduce the Privacy Perception and Reasoning (PPR) framework and construct a bilingual multimodal dataset with synthetic individual profiles, where identifiers (e.g., faces, names) are linked to sensitive attributes. This design enables nine challenging tasks spanning attribute detection, cross-image re-identification, and chained inference. We conduct a large-scale evaluation of over 50 open-source and commercial VLMs. Our analysis shows that 60\\% of widely used VLMs can perform individual-level privacy reasoning with up to 80\\% accuracy, posing a significant threat to personal privacy. MultiPriv provides a foundation for developing and assessing privacy-preserving VLMs.</p>"},{"id":"67059","en":"Position: The Privacy-Auditability Paradox in Federated Learning: Why We Need Controllable Secure Aggregation","ko":"Position: Federated Learning에서의 프라이버시-감사가능성 역설: 왜 제어 가능한 Secure Aggregation이 필요한가","authors":"Runhua Xu, Guoan Wan, James Joshi","pos":"#3211","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=vHCTZ78QUH","abs":"<p>Federated Learning (FL) has become the de facto standard for privacy-preserving intelligence, largely due to Secure Aggregation protocols that guarantee the mathematical invisibility of individual user contributions.  However, we contend that this pursuit of perfect privacy has engineered a systemic vulnerability: the Privacy-Auditability Paradox.  By rendering user updates computationally indistinguishable, current protocols create a \"Sanitization Gap\" where malicious poisoning is undetectable and a \"Regulatory Dead Zone\" where compliance with the EU AI Act's robustness and explainability mandates is mathematically impossible.  In this position paper, we argue that the community must transition from \"Blind Aggregation\" to Controllable Secure Aggregation (CSA).  We propose a cryptographic paradigm shift utilizing Decentralized Multi-Client Functional Encryption and Zero-Knowledge Proofs (ZKPs) to replace binary secrecy with fine-grained policy-based governance.  This framework introduces \"Verified Blindness\", where the server remains blind to raw data by default but possesses a cryptographically regulated \"Break-Glass\" mechanism to audit specific inputs under consensus-based governance.  We conclude that adopting CSA is not merely a technical upgrade but an existential necessity to transform Federated Learning from an unregulated academic concept into robust, compliant, and trustworthy critical infrastructure.</p>"},{"id":"65479","en":"PrivCode++ : Latent-Conditioned Differentially Private Code Generation for Comprehensive Guarantees","ko":"PrivCode++: 포괄적 보장을 위한 잠재 조건부 Differentially Private 코드 생성","authors":"Zheng Liu, Chen GONG, Terry Yue Zhuo, Zhou Yang, Kecen Li, Wenlong Meng, Xinwen Hou, Yu Liu, Xiaochen Li","pos":"#3212","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=DDYr4KXKs1","abs":"<p>Large language models fine-tuned on instruction–code pairs may memorize and subsequently leak sensitive training data. Existing differentially private (DP) code generation methods primarily protect code snippets while assuming prompts are public, which fails in realistic scenarios where prompts may also contain sensitive information. When prompts cannot be explicitly learned or used during generation, code synthesis suffers from severe utility degradation and reduced diversity. To address these challenges, we propose PrivCode++, the first work to explore DP code generation under where both prompts and code snippets are considered sensitive in LLM fine-tuning. PrivCode++ introduces a two-stage DP framework with a Privacy-Free Latent Conditioning module, enabling effective DP fine-tuning and data synthesis without direct access to sensitive prompts or code. Extensive experiments show that PrivCode++ achieves substantially higher utility than baselines, remains competitive with the method with relaxing privacy assumptions, and provides stronger privacy guarantees.</p>"},{"id":"61631","en":"PrivGate: Steering Contextual Integrity in LLMs via Latent Space Geometry","ko":"PrivGate: 잠재 공간 기하를 통한 LLM의 Contextual Integrity 조정","authors":"Runshan Hu, Yukun Dong, Yingying Huangfu, Ruohan Zhao, Yi Xie, Tieyan Li","pos":"#3213","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=oKizUOP7E4","abs":"<p>Securing <em>Contextual Integrity</em> (CI) is critical for privacy-preserving Large Language Model (LLM) agent execution. However, existing agents struggle to balance the agility of direct generation against the prohibitive latency of CI-constrained thinking. To address this, we propose <em>PrivGate</em>, a framework that selectively invokes explicit reasoning based on internal privacy signals. Our approach is grounded in the discovery of a <em>Privacy Manifold</em>, where models linearly encode privacy sensitivity within their residual streams, even during non-compliant generation. Leveraging this structure, <em>PrivGate</em> employs <em>Latent Gating</em>, a training-free mechanism that triggers explicit reasoning only when high latent risk is detected, thereby optimizing the efficiency-privacy trade-off by minimizing unnecessary compute. On the real-world PrivacyLens benchmark, <em>PrivGate</em> achieves an out-of-distribution AUROC of 0.97 in risk identification, confirming the universality of the discovered manifold. End-to-end evaluations show that <em>PrivGate</em> achieves a 70% reduction in privacy leakage with less than 5% overhead, offering a practical pathway to reconcile rigorous CI requirements with the performance demands of LLM agents.</p>","absKo":"<p><em>Contextual Integrity</em>(CI)를 보호하는 것은 privacy-preserving Large Language Model(LLM) agent 실행에 매우 중요하다. 그러나 기존 agent는 direct generation의 민첩성과 CI 제약이 있는 사고의 과도한 latency 사이에서 균형을 맞추는 데 어려움을 겪는다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 내부 privacy signal에 따라 explicit reasoning을 선택적으로 호출하는 framework인 <em>PrivGate</em>를 제안한다. 우리의 접근은 <em>Privacy Manifold</em>의 발견에 기반하며, 여기서 model은 비준수 generation 중에도 residual stream에 privacy sensitivity를 선형적으로 인코딩한다. 이 구조를 활용하여 <em>PrivGate</em>는 <em>Latent Gating</em>을 사용한다. 이는 높은 latent risk가 감지될 때에만 explicit reasoning을 트리거하는 training-free mechanism으로, 불필요한 compute를 최소화하여 efficiency-privacy trade-off를 최적화한다. 실제 PrivacyLens benchmark에서 <em>PrivGate</em>는 risk identification에서 out-of-distribution AUROC 0.97을 달성하여, 발견된 manifold의 보편성을 확인한다. end-to-end 평가에서는 <em>PrivGate</em>가 5% 미만의 overhead로 privacy leakage를 70% 줄이는 것으로 나타나, 엄격한 CI 요구사항과 LLM agent의 성능 요구를 조화시킬 수 있는 실용적 경로를 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"63312","en":"Privacy Amplification in Differentially Private Zeroth-Order Optimization with Hidden States","ko":"은닉 상태를 갖춘 차등 프라이버시 영차 최적화에서의 프라이버시 증폭","authors":"Eli Chien, Wei-Ning Chen, Pan Li","pos":"#3214","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=YBIGgUet07","abs":"<p>Zeroth-order optimization has emerged as a promising approach for fine-tuning large language models on domain-specific data, particularly under differential privacy (DP) and memory constraints. While first-order methods have been extensively studied from a privacy perspective, the privacy analysis and algorithmic design for zeroth-order methods remain significantly underexplored. A critical open question concerns hidden-state DP analysis: although convergent privacy bounds are known for first-order methods, it has remained unclear whether similar guarantees can be established for zeroth-order methods. In this work, we provide an affirmative answer by proving a convergent DP bound for zeroth-order optimization. Our analysis generalizes the celebrated privacy amplification-by-iteration framework to the setting of smooth loss functions in zeroth-order optimization. Furthermore, it induces better DP zeroth-order algorithmic designs that are previously unknown to the literature.</p>","absKo":"<p>Zeroth-order optimization은 domain-specific data에서 large language model을 fine-tuning하는 유망한 접근법으로 부상했으며, 특히 differential privacy (DP)와 memory constraint 하에서 더욱 그렇다. first-order method는 privacy 관점에서 광범위하게 연구되어 왔지만, zeroth-order method에 대한 privacy analysis와 algorithmic design은 여전히 충분히 탐구되지 않았다. 중요한 미해결 질문은 hidden-state DP analysis에 관한 것이다. first-order method에 대해서는 convergent privacy bound가 알려져 있지만, zeroth-order method에서도 유사한 보장을 확립할 수 있는지는 분명하지 않았다. 본 연구에서는 zeroth-order optimization에 대해 convergent DP bound를 증명함으로써 이에 긍정적으로 답한다. 우리의 분석은 유명한 privacy amplification-by-iteration framework를 zeroth-order optimization의 smooth loss function 설정으로 일반화한다. 더 나아가, 이는 문헌에서 이전에 알려지지 않았던 더 나은 DP zeroth-order algorithmic design을 이끈다.</p>"},{"id":"64683","en":"Privacy Risks of Agentic Inferential Capabilities in Data Linkage Attacks","ko":"Data Linkage 공격에서 Agentic 추론 능력의 프라이버시 위험","authors":"Myeongseob Ko, Jihyun Jeong, Sumiran Thakur, Gyuhak Kim, Ruoxi Jia","pos":"#3215","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Kux5q1mL1x","abs":"<p>We present a systematic study and a benchmark of inference-driven linkage risk in LLM-based agents, where identities are reconstructed by aggregating fragmented, individually non-identifying signals. Historically, data linkage attacks required substantial domain expertise and bespoke feature engineering, but agentic reasoning can collapse this barrier, expanding privacy risk beyond memorization or direct leakage.       We evaluate this risk across three settings: reproducing classical Netflix and AOL linkage attacks with agents, introducing a controlled de-anonymization benchmark that varies fingerprint structure and task intent, and analyzing real-world unstructured traces. Agents re-identify 79.2\\% of users on the Netflix dataset (vs. 56.0\\% for the classical heuristic), and on our benchmark, identity hypotheses emerge even under benign task framing and rise sharply under explicit re-identification requests. A privacy-aware system prompt can reduce leakage dramatically for some models (e.g., from 19/20 to 1/20 cases) but incurs utility loss, showing that mitigating inference-driven linkage often comes at a measurable utility cost.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 LLM-based agents에서 inference-driven linkage risk에 대한 체계적 연구와 benchmark를 제시한다. 여기서 개인의 신원은 각각은 식별 가능하지 않은 단편적 신호들을 집계함으로써 재구성된다. 과거의 data linkage attack은 상당한 domain expertise와 맞춤형 feature engineering을 필요로 했지만, agentic reasoning은 이러한 장벽을 무너뜨려 privacy risk를 memorization이나 직접적인 leakage를 넘어 확장시킬 수 있다. 우리는 이 위험을 세 가지 설정에서 평가한다: agents로 classical Netflix 및 AOL linkage attack을 재현하고, fingerprint 구조와 task intent를 달리하는 controlled de-anonymization benchmark를 도입하며, 실제 세계의 unstructured trace를 분석한다. Agents는 Netflix dataset에서 사용자의 79.2\\%를 re-identify하며(classical heuristic의 56.0\\% 대비), 우리 benchmark에서는 benign한 task framing 아래에서도 identity hypothesis가 나타나고 explicit re-identification request에서는 급격히 증가한다. privacy-aware system prompt는 일부 모델에서 leakage를 극적으로 줄일 수 있지만(예: 19/20 case에서 1/20 case로), utility loss를 수반한다. 이는 inference-driven linkage를 완화하는 일이 종종 측정 가능한 utility 비용을 동반함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"62612","en":"Privacy-Aware Data Integration for Enhanced Quantile Inference under Heterogeneity","ko":"이질성 하에서 양적 추론을 강화하는 Privacy-Aware Data Integration","authors":"Leheng Cai, Qirui Hu, Shuyuan Wu","pos":"#3216","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=f3q85c5wkg","abs":"Quantile estimation and inference play essential roles in diverse scientific and industrial applications, and their accuracy can often be enhanced by integrating auxiliary data from multiple sites. However, developing efficient aggregation methods for quantile inference under potential privacy constraints, particularly with heterogeneous datasets, remains challenging. To address these issues, we propose a systematic framework for quantile estimation and inference under potential local differential privacy (LDP). The key idea is to construct weighted estimators by adaptively aggregating quantile estimates from target and source sites. The adaptive weights are determined by minimizing the asymptotic variance, incorporating an additional $\\ell_2$ penalty to account for parameter shift. A parallel stochastic gradient descent algorithm under LDP constraints is developed for weight estimation and valid inference. Additionally, we introduce a conservative weighted estimator to ensure robust inference across diverse heterogeneous scenarios. Rigorous theoretical analysis establishes the consistency, normality, and effectiveness of the proposed methods. Extensive numerical studies and real data application corroborate our theoretical findings.","absKo":"Quantile estimation과 inference는 다양한 과학 및 산업 응용에서 핵심적인 역할을 하며, 여러 site에서 오는 auxiliary data를 통합하면 그 정확도를 종종 향상시킬 수 있다. 그러나 특히 heterogeneous dataset이 존재할 때 privacy constraint 하에서 quantile inference를 위한 효율적인 aggregation 방법을 개발하는 것은 여전히 어렵다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 potential local differential privacy(LDP) 하에서의 quantile estimation 및 inference를 위한 체계적인 framework를 제안한다. 핵심 아이디어는 target site와 source site의 quantile estimate를 적응적으로 집계하여 weighted estimator를 구성하는 것이다. adaptive weight는 parameter shift를 반영하기 위한 추가적인 $\\ell_2$ penalty를 포함하여 asymptotic variance를 최소화하도록 결정된다. LDP 제약 하에서 weight estimation과 valid inference를 위한 parallel stochastic gradient descent 알고리즘도 개발하였다. 또한, 다양한 heterogeneous scenario 전반에서 견고한 inference를 보장하기 위해 conservative weighted estimator를 도입한다. 엄밀한 이론적 분석을 통해 제안 방법의 consistency, normality, effectiveness를 확립한다. 광범위한 수치 실험과 실제 데이터 적용은 우리의 이론적 결과를 뒷받침한다."},{"id":"63482","en":"Differentially Private Submodular Maximization with a Knapsack Constraint","ko":"배낭 제약을 갖춘 차등 프라이버시 서브모듈러 최대화","authors":"Ron Zadicario, Tova Milo","pos":"#3300","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Wph27Qttp5","abs":"Submodular maximization subject to a knapsack constraint (SMK) is a fundamental problem in discrete optimization, with wide-ranging applications in machine learning and related fields. As these applications increasingly involve sensitive individual data, there is a growing need for high-utility algorithms that provide formal privacy guarantees. In this work, we study the SMK problem under differential privacy, considering both monotone and non-monotone objective functions. For monotone objectives, we propose a differentially private algorithm that achieves the optimal $(1-1/e)$-approximation ratio while significantly improving both additive error and query complexity over prior work. We also present a more efficient variant attaining a $1/2$-approximation. For non-monotone objectives, we introduce, to our knowledge, the first differentially private algorithm with provable guarantees, achieving a $1/4$-approximation in expectation and an additive error comparable to the best known for monotone objectives.","absKo":"knapsack constraint를 받는 submodular maximization(SMK)은 이산 최적화의 근본적인 문제로, machine learning 및 관련 분야 전반에 걸쳐 폭넓게 활용된다. 이러한 응용이 점점 더 민감한 개인 데이터를 포함함에 따라, 형식적인 privacy guarantee를 제공하면서도 높은 utility를 갖는 알고리즘에 대한 요구가 커지고 있다. 본 연구에서는 monotone 및 non-monotone objective function을 모두 고려하여 differential privacy 하의 SMK 문제를 다룬다. monotone objective에 대해서는, 기존 연구보다 additive error와 query complexity를 크게 개선하면서 최적의 $(1-1/e)$-approximation ratio를 달성하는 differentially private 알고리즘을 제안한다. 또한 더 효율적인 변형으로 $1/2$-approximation을 달성하는 방법도 제시한다. non-monotone objective에 대해서는, 우리가 아는 한 provable guarantee를 갖는 최초의 differentially private 알고리즘을 도입하며, 기대값 기준 $1/4$-approximation과 monotone objective에서 알려진 최선 수준과 비슷한 additive error를 달성한다."},{"id":"64139","en":"Differentially Private Range Subgraph Counting","ko":"차등 프라이버시 범위 부분그래프 계수","authors":"Xian Chen, Ruobing Bai, Pan Peng","pos":"#3301","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=QYpByrxSTg","abs":"<p>Subgraph counting is a fundamental problem in graph analysis. Motivated by practical scenarios where graph analytics are performed on subgraphs induced by selected vertices -- rather than on the entire graph -- and by growing privacy concerns, we initiate the study of <em>differentially private range subgraph counting (DPRSC)</em>. The goal is to privately count occurrences of a fixed pattern graph within induced subgraphs defined by multi-dimensional attribute ranges. Unlike classical point counting, subgraph counting is inherently nonlinear and exhibits high sensitivity: a single edge modification can affect many subgraph occurrences.  We present the first efficient algorithms for DPRSC with small additive error. Our approach introduces a subgraph projection that reduces DPRSC to weighted orthogonal range counting, enabling the use of range trees and local sensitivity estimation to achieve accurate private query answering. We complement our algorithms with matching lower bounds, obtained by reducing reconstruction attacks to DPRSC and leveraging discrepancy theory. In particular, we show that any differentially private algorithm for DPRSC must incur additive error exponential in the dimension. Empirical evaluations demonstrate that our algorithms significantly outperform baseline methods in accuracy while maintaining strong privacy guarantees.</p>","absKo":"<p>subgraph counting은 graph analysis의 근본적인 문제이다. 전체 graph가 아니라 선택된 vertex가 유도하는 subgraph에서 graph analytics를 수행하는 실제 상황과 점점 커지는 privacy concern에 동기를 얻어, 우리는 <em>differentially private range subgraph counting(DPRSC)</em>의 연구를 시작한다. 목표는 다차원 attribute range로 정의된 induced subgraph 안에서 특정 pattern graph의 발생 횟수를 비공개로 세는 것이다. 고전적인 point counting과 달리, subgraph counting은 본질적으로 비선형이며 sensitivity가 높다. 단일 edge 수정만으로도 많은 subgraph 발생 횟수에 영향을 줄 수 있다. 우리는 작은 additive error를 갖는 DPRSC를 위한 최초의 효율적 알고리즘을 제시한다. 우리의 접근은 DPRSC를 weighted orthogonal range counting으로 축소하는 subgraph projection을 도입하며, 이를 통해 range tree와 local sensitivity estimation을 활용하여 정확한 private query answering을 달성한다. 또한 reconstruction attack을 DPRSC로 환원하고 discrepancy theory를 활용하여 대응하는 lower bound를 제시한다. 특히 DPRSC를 위한 어떤 differentially private algorithm도 차원에 대해 exponential한 additive error를 피할 수 없음을 보인다. 실험 평가에서는 우리의 알고리즘이 강한 privacy guarantee를 유지하면서 accuracy 측면에서 baseline 방법들을 현저히 능가함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"61746","en":"Differentially Private Geodesic Regression","ko":"차등개인정보보호 Geodesic 회귀","authors":"Aditya Kulkarni, Carlos Soto","pos":"#3302","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=nGlwpZFZre","abs":"In statistical applications it has become increasingly common to encounter data structures that live on non-linear spaces such as manifolds. Classical linear regression, one of the most fundamental methodologies of statistical learning, captures the relationship between an independent variable and a response variable which both are assumed to live in Euclidean space. Thus, geodesic regression emerged as an extension where the response variable lives on a Riemannian manifold. The parameters of geodesic regression, as with linear regression, capture the relationship of sensitive data and hence one should consider the privacy protection practices of said parameters. We consider releasing Differentially Private (DP) parameters of geodesic regression via the K-Norm Gradient (KNG) mechanism for Riemannian manifolds. We derive theoretical bounds for the sensitivity of the parameters showing they are tied to their respective Jacobi fields and hence the curvature of the space. This corroborates, and extends, recent findings of differential privacy for the Fr\\'echet mean. We demonstrate the efficacy of our methodology on the sphere, $S_2\\subset\\mathbb{R}^3$, the space of symmetric positive definite matrices, and Kendall's planar shape space. Our methodology is general to any Riemannian manifold, and thus, it is suitable for data in domains such as medical imaging and computer vision.","absKo":"통계 응용에서 manifold와 같은 비선형 공간에 놓인 데이터 구조를 접하는 일이 점점 더 흔해지고 있다. 통계적 학습의 가장 근본적인 방법론 중 하나인 고전적 선형 회귀는 독립변수와 반응변수의 관계를 포착하며, 두 변수는 모두 Euclidean space에 존재한다고 가정한다. 이에 따라 반응변수가 Riemannian manifold 위에 놓이는 확장으로 geodesic regression이 등장했다. geodesic regression의 파라미터는 선형 회귀와 마찬가지로 민감한 데이터와의 관계를 포착하므로, 해당 파라미터에 대한 프라이버시 보호 방식을 고려해야 한다. 우리는 Riemannian manifold에 대해 K-Norm Gradient (KNG) 메커니즘을 사용하여 geodesic regression의 Differentially Private (DP) 파라미터를 공개하는 문제를 다룬다. 우리는 파라미터의 sensitivity에 대한 이론적 경계를 유도하고, 이들이 각 Jacobi field와 따라서 공간의 curvature에 연결됨을 보인다. 이는 Fr\\'echet mean에 대한 differential privacy의 최근 결과를 뒷받침함과 동시에 확장한다. 우리는 sphere, $S_2\\subset\\mathbb{R}^3$, symmetric positive definite matrices의 공간, 그리고 Kendall의 planar shape space에서 본 방법의 효용을 입증한다. 우리의 방법론은 모든 Riemannian manifold에 일반적으로 적용되므로, medical imaging과 computer vision과 같은 도메인의 데이터에 적합하다."},{"id":"64111","en":"Differentially Private Cross-Silo Recommendation from Implicit Feedback","ko":"암묵적 피드백으로부터의 차등 프라이버시 크로스 사일로 추천","authors":"Xun Ran, Qingqing Ye, Xin Huang, Jianliang Xu, Haibo Hu","pos":"#3303","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Qo7ENqEdq9","abs":"<p>Cross-silo recommendation from implicit feedback is a key task in modern recommender systems, where user-item interaction data are distributed across multiple parties and cannot be centrally collected. Unlike explicit feedback, which provides fully observed real-valued ratings, implicit feedback is one-class and extremely sparse, recording only users' actions or inactions (e.g., clicks, visits, or bookmarks), yet it is far more prevalent in real-world applications. Such behavioral data are often highly sensitive, raising significant privacy concerns when used for collaborative model training. Although differential privacy (DP) has been widely applied to explicit feedback-based models, the resulting utility degradation makes it difficult to apply DP effectively to implicit feedback learning. In this work, we propose DPIMF, a differentially private implicit matrix factorization framework for cross-silo recommendation based on objective perturbation. To improve utility, we redesign the loss function and adopt an importance sampling scheme to reduce the noise scale required for privacy preservation. We further provide formal utility guarantees for the proposed techniques and characterize the conditions under which utility improvements are maximized. Experiments on three benchmark datasets validate our theoretical analysis and demonstrate that DPIMF achieves a better privacy-utility trade-off than state-of-the-art methods.</p>","absKo":"<p>implicit feedback에 기반한 cross-silo recommendation은 modern recommender system의 핵심 과제로, user-item interaction data가 여러 party에 분산되어 있어 중앙에서 수집할 수 없다. fully observed real-valued rating을 제공하는 explicit feedback과 달리, implicit feedback은 one-class이며 극도로 희소하고, 사용자의 행동 또는 비행동(예: click, visit, bookmark)만을 기록하지만 실제 응용에서는 훨씬 더 널리 쓰인다. 이러한 behavioral data는 종종 매우 민감하여 collaborative model training에 사용할 때 중대한 privacy concern을 야기한다. differential privacy(DP)는 explicit feedback 기반 모델에 널리 적용되어 왔지만, 그에 따른 utility 저하는 implicit feedback 학습에 DP를 효과적으로 적용하기 어렵게 만든다. 본 연구에서는 objective perturbation에 기반한 cross-silo recommendation용 differentially private implicit matrix factorization framework인 DPIMF를 제안한다. utility를 향상시키기 위해, 우리는 loss function을 재설계하고 privacy 보장을 위해 필요한 noise scale을 줄이기 위한 importance sampling scheme을 채택한다. 또한 제안 기법에 대한 formal utility guarantee를 제시하고 utility 개선이 최대화되는 조건을 규명한다. 세 개의 benchmark dataset에서 수행한 실험은 우리의 이론 분석을 검증하며, DPIMF가 state-of-the-art 방법보다 더 나은 privacy-utility trade-off를 달성함을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"63209","en":"DP-KFC: Data-Free Preconditioning for Privacy-Preserving Deep Learning","ko":"DP-KFC: 프라이버시 보존 딥러닝을 위한 데이터 프리 전처리","authors":"Marc Molina Van den bosch, Riccardo Taiello, Albert Aillet, Andrea Protani, Miguel Angel Gonzalez Ballester, Luigi Serio","pos":"#3304","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Z6HxJqAzbp","abs":"Differentially private optimization suffers from a fundamental geometric mismatch: deep networks have highly anisotropic loss landscapes, yet DP-SGD injects isotropic noise. Second-order preconditioning can resolve this, but estimating curvature typically requires private data (consuming privacy budget) or public data (introducing distribution shift). We show that the Fisher Information Matrix decouples into *architectural sensitivity*, recoverable via synthetic noise, and *input correlations*, approximable from modality-specific frequency statistics. We propose DP-KFC, which constructs KFAC preconditioners by probing networks with structured synthetic noise, requiring neither private nor public data. Empirically, DP-KFC consistently outperforms DP-SGD and adaptive baselines across diverse modalities in strong privacy regimes ($\\varepsilon \\leq 3$). DP-KFC matches private-data preconditioners while public-data variants degrade by up to $4.8$ %, showing that curvature can be estimated without consuming privacy budget or introducing distribution shift. This enables privacy-preserving learning in specialized domains (e.g., medical applications) where regulatory constraints make data scarce.","absKo":"차등 프라이버시 최적화는 근본적인 기하학적 불일치로 어려움을 겪는다. 딥 네트워크는 매우 비등방적인 손실 지형을 가지지만, DP-SGD는 등방성 노이즈를 주입한다. 2차 전처리는 이를 해결할 수 있지만, 곡률을 추정하려면 일반적으로 private data가 필요해 privacy budget을 소모하거나, public data가 필요해 distribution shift를 유발한다. 우리는 Fisher Information Matrix가 *architectural sensitivity*와 *input correlations*로 분해되며, 전자는 synthetic noise로 복원 가능하고 후자는 modality-specific frequency statistics로 근사 가능함을 보인다. 우리는 DP-KFC를 제안하는데, 이는 구조화된 synthetic noise로 네트워크를 probing하여 KFAC preconditioner를 구성하며, private data도 public data도 필요로 하지 않는다. 실험적으로 DP-KFC는 강한 privacy regime($\\varepsilon \\leq 3$)에서 다양한 modality 전반에 걸쳐 DP-SGD와 adaptive baseline을 일관되게 능가한다. DP-KFC는 private-data preconditioner와 동등한 성능을 보이는 반면, public-data variant는 최대 $4.8$%까지 성능이 저하되어, privacy budget을 소모하거나 distribution shift를 유발하지 않고도 곡률을 추정할 수 있음을 보여준다. 이는 규제 제약으로 인해 데이터가 부족한 의료 응용과 같은 특수 도메인에서 privacy-preserving learning을 가능하게 한다."},{"id":"65780","en":"Beyond Sample-Level Forgetting: Improving Reliability in Multimodal Unlearning","ko":"표본 수준 망각을 넘어서: 멀티모달 언러닝의 신뢰성 향상","authors":"Jianzhou Wang, Yirui Wu, Lixin Yuan, WENXIAO ZHANG, Jun Liu","pos":"#3305","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ADE3kRAise","abs":"<p>Multimodal unlearning aims to eliminate specific data from pretrained multimodal models, which offers significant advantages in data privacy and model efficiency. Current methods struggle to achieve the desired properties of effectiveness, reliability and locality, due to the complex interdependency of unimodal and multimodal knowledge. By introducing a causal perspective, we propose multimodal unlearning with decoupled knowledge components. To promote fine-grained understanding of multimodal context, we introduce Multimodal Variational Inference (MVI) to infer modal-specific and -consistent factors with incomplete sample observation. With foundation of decoupled knowledge, we propose contrastive semantic editing to regulate multimodal unlearning towards refined forgetting. Experiments on privacy- and copyright-sensitive scenarios validate effectiveness of our method across multiple scenarios, ensuring the unlearned model maintains high reliability and locality.</p>"},{"id":"65910","en":"An Empirical Study on the Resilience of Partial Merging to Model Clone Attacks","ko":"부분 병합의 모델 복제 공격에 대한 복원력에 관한 실증 연구","authors":"Tiantong Wu, Yurong Hao, Wei Yang Bryan Lim","pos":"#3306","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=90a2FQiDDQ","abs":"<p>Model merging is a promising technique to enhance the capabilities of neural networks (NNs) by integrating multiple downstream fine-tuned models without requiring access to clients' raw data or substantial computation resources. However, conventional model merging typically requires collecting the full set of fine-tuned model parameters from multiple clients, which may expose them to model-privacy risks. An emerging approach, known as partial model merging (PMM), mitigates this risk by splitting each model into private and shared parts, where only the shared part is merged while the private part remains local to each client. Despite its stricter parameter fusion, PMM can still achieve competitive performance compared to full-parameter sharing. However, the privacy properties of PMM remain underexplored. In this paper, we propose a novel model clone attack and assess the risk of reconstructing the unshared private part of a partially merged model under eight attack scenarios with varying prior knowledge (i.e., partial training data, model parameters and/or model structure). Our comprehensive experiments reveal that merging NNs without adequate protection is highly vulnerable. Even when only a small fraction of training data, model parameters, or model structure is exposed, adversaries can still recover significant portions of the private model's performance.</p>"},{"id":"66440","en":"Accurate, private, secure, federated U-statistics with higher degree","ko":"정확하고 프라이빗하며 안전한 고차 Federated U-통계량","authors":"Quentin Sinh, Jan Ramon","pos":"#3307","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=3i4xYPxtTf","abs":"We study the problem of computing a U-statistic with a kernel function $f$ of degree $k \\geq 2$, i.e.,  the average of some function $f$ over all $k$-tuples of instances,  in a federated learning setting.   U-statistics of degree $2$ include several useful statistics such as Kendall's $\\tau$ coefficient,  the Area under the Receiver-Operator Curve and the Gini mean difference.  Existing methods provide solutions only under the lower-utility local differential privacy model and/or scale poorly in the size of the domain discretization.  In this work, we propose a protocol that securely computes U-statistics of degree $k \\geq 2$ under central differential privacy by leveraging Multi Party Computation (MPC). Our method substantially improves accuracy when compared to prior solutions.   We provide a detailed theoretical analysis of its accuracy, communication and computational properties. We evaluate its performance empirically, obtaining favorable results, e.g., for Kendall's $\\tau$ coefficient, our approach reduces the Mean Squared Error by up to four orders of magnitude over existing baselines."},{"id":"61561","en":"Every Step Counts: Decoding Trajectories as Authorship Fingerprints of dLLMs","ko":"모든 Step이 중요하다: dLLM의 저자 지문으로서 Decoding Trajectory","authors":"Qi Li, Runpeng Yu, Haiquan Lu, Xinchao Wang","pos":"#3414","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=otHlsN1pvk","abs":"<p>Discrete Diffusion Large Language Models (dLLMs) have recently emerged as a promising non-autoregressive paradigm, offering faster inference while achieving strong performance in code generation and mathematical reasoning tasks. In this work, we show that dLLMs’ decoding mechanism not only improves utility but also enables effective model attribution: by analyzing a response’s decoding trajectory, we can identify its source model and help mitigate risks from model misuse. A key challenge is the diversity of attribution scenarios, ranging from distinguishing different models to identifying different checkpoints or backups of the same model. To ensure broad applicability, we focus on two core questions: what information to extract from the decoding trajectory, and how to use it effectively. We first observe that per-step model confidence is ineffective, as the bidirectional nature of dLLMs causes mutual influence among decoded tokens, leading to highly redundant confidence signals that obscure structural information about decoding order and dependencies. To overcome this, we propose a novel information extraction scheme called the \\textit{Directed Decoding Map (DDM)}, which captures structural relationships between decoding steps and reveals model-specific behaviors. Furthermore, to fully leverage the extracted structure, we propose \\textit{Gaussian-Trajectory Attribution (GTA)}, which fits a cell-wise Gaussian distribution at each decoding position for each model and uses log-likelihood differences between trajectories as the attribution score. Extensive experiments across diverse models, datasets and different model access assumptions validate the effectiveness of our approach.</p>","absKo":"<p>Discrete Diffusion Large Language Models(dLLMs)는 최근 유망한 non-autoregressive paradigm으로 부상했으며, code generation과 수학적 추론 과제에서 강한 성능을 보이면서 더 빠른 inference를 제공한다. 본 연구에서는 dLLM의 decoding mechanism이 utility를 향상시킬 뿐 아니라 효과적인 model attribution도 가능하게 함을 보인다. 응답의 decoding trajectory를 분석함으로써 소스 model을 식별하고 model misuse로부터의 위험을 완화하는 데 도움을 줄 수 있다. 핵심 과제는 서로 다른 model을 구분하는 것부터 동일한 model의 서로 다른 checkpoint나 backup을 식별하는 것까지 attribution 시나리오가 매우 다양하다는 점이다. 폭넓은 적용 가능성을 보장하기 위해, 우리는 두 가지 핵심 질문에 초점을 맞춘다: decoding trajectory에서 무엇을 추출할 것인가, 그리고 그것을 어떻게 효과적으로 사용할 것인가. 먼저, 단계별 model confidence는 효과적이지 않음을 관찰한다. dLLM의 양방향성 때문에 decoded token 간 상호 영향이 발생하여, decoding 순서와 의존성의 구조 정보를 가리는 매우 중복적인 confidence signal이 만들어지기 때문이다. 이를 극복하기 위해, 우리는 decoding step 간 구조적 관계를 포착하고 model-specific behavior를 드러내는 \\textit{Directed Decoding Map(DDM)}이라는 새로운 정보 추출 scheme을 제안한다. 나아가 추출된 구조를 충분히 활용하기 위해, 각 model에 대해 각 decoding position마다 cell-wise Gaussian distribution을 적합하고 trajectory 간 log-likelihood 차이를 attribution score로 사용하는 \\textit{Gaussian-Trajectory Attribution(GTA)}을 제안한다. 다양한 model, dataset, 그리고 서로 다른 model access assumption 전반에 걸친 광범위한 실험이 우리 접근법의 효과를 검증한다.</p>"},{"id":"66734","en":"Shift-Dependent Asymmetry: Orthogonal Inverse Low-Rank Adaptation for Federated Medical Segmentation","ko":"Shift 의존적 비대칭성: Federated 의료 분할을 위한 Orthogonal Inverse Low-Rank Adaptation","authors":"Xingyue Zhao, Wenke Huang, Linghao Zhuang, Haoran Wu, Anwen Jiang, Zhifeng Wang, Wenwen He, Ming Feng, Mang Ye, Bo XU","pos":"#4402","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=0wxnefBSTB","abs":"<p>Low-Rank Adaptation (LoRA) enables efficient federated fine-tuning of segmentation foundation models for medical imaging. However, most federated LoRA methods adopt a uniform aggregation rule, which breaks under the encoder–decoder asymmetry in medical segmentation: the encoder is dominated by appearance shifts, while the decoder is dominated by supervision variations. This mismatch entangles shared anatomy with site-specific biases and harms generalization. To address this, we propose Inverse Asymmetric Tuning (IAT). IAT aligns adaptation with heterogeneity sources by selectively personalizing module-specific adaptation components in the encoder to absorb acquisition-driven appearance shifts and in the decoder to accommodate site-dependent supervision, while retaining a shared pathway for transferable consensus. However, structural separation alone is insufficient under LoRA’s bilinear parameterization, where multiplicative coupling can still cause site-specific updates to leak into the shared update direction. We therefore introduce a Subspace Orthogonality Regularizer that penalizes shared–local collinearity in the effective update space, mitigating leakage without increasing communication. Extensive experiments demonstrate consistent improvements over strong federated LoRA and parameter-efficient FL baselines.</p>"},{"id":"61220","en":"Furina: Fragmented Uncertainty-Driven Refusal Instability Attack","ko":"Furina: 파편화된 불확실성 기반 거절 불안정성 공격","authors":"Tongxi Wu, Jian Zhang, Yang Gao","pos":"#3107","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=sY418Hdtrw","abs":"<p>Safety alignment in large language models (LLMs) and multimodal large language models (MLLMs) is commonly assumed to operate as a near-binary threshold mechanism. We challenge this assumption by revealing that safety behavior is governed by an \\emph{instability region} where small perturbations induce stochastic refusal decisions rather than deterministic outcomes. We develop a multi-metric diagnostic framework combining external and internal signals to characterize this instability. Through systematic experiments, we identify a characteristic \\emph{diagnostic signature}: inputs in unstable regimes exhibit elevated output uncertainty yet \\emph{decreased} internal safety activation, a decoupling phenomenon that explains why detection-based defenses fail against sophisticated attacks. Building on this framework, we introduce \\textbf{Furina}, a jailbreak attack that deliberately induces this signature through fragmented, scene-anchored prompts without model-specific optimization. Furina outperforms strong single-turn and multi-turn baselines on HarmBench and achieves competitive results on MM-SafetyBench, demonstrating that uncertainty amplification provides a principled and transferable mechanism for understanding safety vulnerabilities. Code and supplementary materials: \\url{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/Furina_Jailbreak-EF7C}.</p>","absKo":"<p>large language models (LLMs)와 multimodal large language models (MLLMs)의 safety alignment는 흔히 거의 이진적인 threshold mechanism으로 작동한다고 가정된다. 우리는 이 가정에 도전하며, 작은 perturbation이 결정론적 결과가 아니라 확률적 refusal decision을 유도하는 \\emph{instability region}이 안전 행동을 지배한다는 사실을 밝힌다. 우리는 외부 및 내부 신호를 결합한 multi-metric diagnostic framework를 개발하여 이러한 불안정성을 특징지었다. 체계적인 실험을 통해 우리는 특징적인 \\emph{diagnostic signature}를 확인했다. 즉, 불안정한 regime의 입력은 출력 불확실성이 증가하는 동시에 내부 safety activation은 \\emph{감소}하는데, 이러한 분리 현상이 정교한 attack에 대해 detection-based defense가 실패하는 이유를 설명한다. 이 framework를 바탕으로, 우리는 model-specific optimization 없이 fragmented되고 scene-anchored된 prompt를 통해 의도적으로 이 signature를 유도하는 jailbreak attack인 \\textbf{Furina}를 소개한다. Furina는 HarmBench에서 강력한 single-turn 및 multi-turn baseline을 능가하고, MM-SafetyBench에서도 경쟁력 있는 결과를 달성하여, uncertainty amplification이 safety vulnerability를 이해하는 데 있어 원리적이고 전이 가능한 메커니즘임을 보여준다. 코드와 부록 자료: \\url{https://anonymous.4open.science/r/Furina_Jailbreak-EF7C}.</p>"},{"id":"64616","en":"STARE: Step-wise Temporal Alignment and Red-teaming Engine for Multi-modal Toxicity Attack","ko":"STARE: 멀티모달 독성 공격을 위한 단계별 Temporal Alignment 및 Red-teaming Engine","authors":"Xutao Mao, Liangjie Zhao, Liutao, Xiang Zheng, Hongying Zan, Cong Wang","pos":"#4517","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Leijxx6Czi","abs":"Red-teaming Vision-Language Models is essential for identifying vulnerabilities where adversarial image-text inputs trigger toxic outputs. Existing approaches treat image generation as a black box, providing only terminal toxicity scores while remaining temporally opaque regarding when and how toxic semantics emerge during multi-step synthesis.  We introduce $\\textbf{STARE}$, a hierarchical reinforcement learning framework that treats the denoising trajectory as an exploitable attack surface. By synergizing a high-level prompt editor with low-level T2I fine-tuning via Group Relative Policy Optimization (GRPO), STARE achieves a 68\\% improvement in Attack Success Rate over state-of-the-art baselines including black box and white-box variants. More importantly, we reveal the Optimization-Induced Phase Alignment phenomenon: while vanilla models exhibit diffuse toxicity, adversarial optimization systematically concentrates conceptual harms into early semantic phases and detail-oriented harms into late refinement. This discovery transforms toxicity formation from a chaotic process into a series of predictable vulnerability windows. This temporal alignment transforms red-teaming from a trial-and-error process into a targeted structural analysis. Our work provides both a potent attack engine and a diagnostic foundation for developing next-generation, phase-aware safety mechanisms. Content warning: This paper contains examples of toxic content that may be offensive or disturbing.","absKo":"Red-teaming Vision-Language Models는 adversarial image-text input이 toxic output을 유발하는 취약성을 식별하는 데 필수적이다. 기존 접근법은 image generation을 black box로 취급하여, 최종 toxicity score만 제공하고 multi-step synthesis 동안 독성 의미가 언제, 어떻게 나타나는지에 대해서는 시간적으로 불투명하다. 우리는 denoising trajectory를 악용 가능한 attack surface로 취급하는 hierarchical reinforcement learning framework인 $\\textbf{STARE}$를 소개한다. Group Relative Policy Optimization (GRPO)을 통한 high-level prompt editor와 low-level T2I fine-tuning을 시너지 있게 결합함으로써, STARE는 black box 및 white-box 변형을 포함한 state-of-the-art baseline 대비 Attack Success Rate를 68\\% 향상시킨다. 더욱 중요한 것은, 우리는 Optimization-Induced Phase Alignment 현상을 밝혀냈다는 점이다. vanilla model이 확산된 toxicity를 보이는 반면, adversarial optimization은 개념적 harm을 초기 semantic phase에, 세부 묘사 중심의 harm을 후기 refinement 단계에 체계적으로 집중시킨다. 이 발견은 toxicity 형성을 혼란스러운 과정에서 예측 가능한 일련의 vulnerability window로 바꾼다. 이러한 temporal alignment는 red-teaming을 시행착오 과정에서 표적화된 구조적 분석으로 전환한다. 우리의 연구는 강력한 attack engine과 함께, 차세대 phase-aware safety mechanism 개발을 위한 진단적 기반을 제공한다. Content warning: 이 논문에는 offensive하거나 불쾌하거나 충격적일 수 있는 toxic content 예시가 포함되어 있다."},{"id":"64726","en":"TimeGuard: Channel-wise Pool Training for Backdoor Defense in Time Series Forecasting","ko":"TimeGuard: 시계열 예측에서 Backdoor 방어를 위한 Channel-wise Pool 학습","authors":"Quang Duc Nguyen, Siyuan Liang, Yiming Li, Fushuo Huo, Dacheng Tao","pos":"#3101","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=KSF8Q492oV","abs":"Time Series Forecasting (TSF) plays a critical role across many domains, yet it is vulnerable to backdoor attacks. However, backdoor defenses tailored to TSF remain underexplored, due to data entanglement and task-formulation shift challenges. To fill this gap, we conduct a systematic evaluation of thirteen representative backdoor defenses across the TSF life cycle and analyze their failure modes. Our results reveal two fundamental issues: (1) data entanglement induces *channel-level signal dilution*, rendering sample-filtering and trigger-synthesis defenses ineffective at localizing backdoors; and (2) task-formulation shift leads to *training-loss degeneration*, causing poisoned and clean windows to become indistinguishable at training stages. Based on these findings, we propose a training-time backdoor defense for TSF, termed TimeGuard. Our method adopts channel-wise pool training as the core paradigm and initializes a high-confidence pool using time-aware criteria to mitigate signal dilution. Moreover, we introduce distance-regularized loss selection to progressively expand the reliable pool during training and ease loss degeneration. Extensive experiments across multiple datasets, forecasting architectures, and TSF backdoor attacks demonstrate that TimeGuard substantially improves robustness, boosting $\\mathrm{MAE}\\_\\mathrm{P}$ by 1.96× over the leading baseline, while preserving clean performance within 5% $\\mathrm{MAE}\\_\\mathrm{C}$.","absKo":"Time Series Forecasting (TSF)은 많은 도메인에서 중요한 역할을 하지만, backdoor attack에 취약합니다. 그러나 TSF에 특화된 backdoor defense는 data entanglement와 task-formulation shift라는 도전 때문에 아직 충분히 연구되지 않았습니다. 이 간극을 메우기 위해, 우리는 TSF 라이프사이클 전반에 걸쳐 13개의 대표적인 backdoor defense를 체계적으로 평가하고 그 실패 모드를 분석합니다. 우리의 결과는 두 가지 근본적 문제를 드러냅니다. (1) data entanglement는 *channel-level signal dilution*을 유발하여 sample-filtering 및 trigger-synthesis defense가 backdoor를 국소화하는 것을 무력화하고, (2) task-formulation shift는 *training-loss degeneration*을 초래하여 학습 단계에서 poisoned window와 clean window를 구분 불가능하게 만듭니다. 이러한 발견을 바탕으로, 우리는 TSF를 위한 training-time backdoor defense인 TimeGuard를 제안합니다. 우리의 방법은 channel-wise pool training을 핵심 패러다임으로 채택하고, signal dilution을 완화하기 위해 time-aware criteria로 high-confidence pool을 초기화합니다. 또한 distance-regularized loss selection을 도입하여 학습 중 신뢰 가능한 pool을 점진적으로 확장하고 loss degeneration을 완화합니다. 여러 데이터셋, forecasting architecture, TSF backdoor attack에 걸친 광범위한 실험은 TimeGuard가 robust를 크게 향상시키며, 선도 baseline 대비 $\\mathrm{MAE}\\_\\mathrm{P}$를 1.96× 개선하는 동시에 clean performance를 $\\mathrm{MAE}\\_\\mathrm{C}$ 기준 5% 이내로 유지함을 보여줍니다."},{"id":"61385","en":"MADA-Attack: Transferable Multi-modal Attention Distraction Adversarial Attack against Vision Language Models","ko":"MADA-Attack: Vision Language Models에 대한 전이 가능한 Multi-modal Attention Distraction Adversarial Attack","authors":"Zhihan Qin, Jiahao Chen, Chunyi Zhou, Yuwen Pu, Chunqiang Hu, Xiaolei Liu, Shouling Ji","pos":"#3103","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ql0gSFEKAC","abs":"<p>Vision Language Models (VLMs) achieve strong performance across multi-modal tasks but remain vulnerable to universal adversarial perturbations (UAPs). Existing UAP methods mainly operate on the visual modality, overlooking structured textual semantics and cross-modal interactions, which limits their ability to disrupt alignment and generalize across tasks and model architectures. To address these limits, we propose <strong>Multi-modal Attention Distraction Adversarial Attack (MADA-Attack)</strong> framework. We begin by conducting several insight experiments and discover that modality attention distributes differently over layers and early phase of optimization is decisive. Building on these observations, we introduce Semantic Token Manipulation (STM) to steer text-guided attention, and Fused Embedding Training (FET) to jointly optimize textual and visual embedding losses for coordinated misalignment. We further incorporate an Adaptive Data Augmentation (ADA) strategy that dynamically balances attack strength, transferability, and training efficiency. Extensive experiments demonstrate that <strong>MADA-Attack</strong> consistently achieves state-of-the-art performance and strong transferability while remaining computationally lightweight, with an average ASR of 82.60\\% and 73.42\\% in zero-shot classification and image captioning tasks. For the visual question answering (VQA) and I-T Retrieval task, our method exceeds the SOTA baseline by 10\\%. Our code will be available soon.</p>","absKo":"<p>Vision Language Models (VLMs)는 multi-modal task 전반에서 강한 성능을 보이지만, universal adversarial perturbation (UAP)에 대해서는 여전히 취약하다. 기존 UAP 방법은 주로 visual modality에만 작동하며, 구조화된 textual semantics와 cross-modal interaction을 간과한다. 이로 인해 alignment를 교란하고 task 및 model architecture 전반으로 일반화하는 능력이 제한된다. 이러한 한계를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 <strong>Multi-modal Attention Distraction Adversarial Attack (MADA-Attack)</strong> framework를 제안한다. 먼저 여러 insight experiment를 수행한 결과, modality attention이 layer별로 다르게 분포하며 optimization 초기 phase가 결정적이라는 사실을 발견했다. 이러한 관찰을 바탕으로, text-guided attention을 유도하기 위한 Semantic Token Manipulation (STM)과, textual 및 visual embedding loss를 공동으로 최적화하여 coordinated misalignment를 유도하는 Fused Embedding Training (FET)을 도입한다. 또한 attack strength, transferability, training efficiency 사이를 동적으로 균형 조절하는 Adaptive Data Augmentation (ADA) 전략을 통합한다. 광범위한 실험은 <strong>MADA-Attack</strong>이 계산적으로 가벼우면서도 consistently state-of-the-art performance와 강한 transferability를 달성함을 보여준다. zero-shot classification과 image captioning task에서 평균 ASR은 각각 82.60\\%, 73.42\\%에 달한다. visual question answering (VQA) 및 I-T Retrieval task에서는 우리의 방법이 SOTA baseline을 10\\% 초과한다. 코드는 곧 공개될 예정이다.</p>"},{"id":"62015","en":"Adversarial Attack and Defense for Denoising Diffusion Sampling","ko":"Denoising Diffusion sampling을 위한 adversarial attack 및 defense","authors":"Zhao-Rong Lai, Xiwen Yuan, Jian Weng","pos":"#3104","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=khMSeuLLhh","abs":"<p>Denoising diffusion sampling (DDS) is an emerging approach for generating new samples that have the same distribution as some training samples. However, it is vulnerable to adversarial attacks by even a Gaussian perturbation. In this work, we propose a complete set of adversarial attack and defense methodology for DDS. In the attack side, we propose to inject a perturbation to the sampling stage, which significantly worsen the performance of sample generation. In the defense side, we propose a local variation based regularization model for the potential function minimization, which effectively tolerates the adversarial perturbations. Moreover, we develop a conjugate gradient algorithm to solve the defense model, which integrates with a recently-developed zeroth order rejection sampling method that saves computational cost. Experimental results show that the proposed attack significantly worsen the existing state-of-the-art methods, but can be defended by the proposed local variation regularization.</p>","absKo":"<p>Denoising diffusion sampling (DDS)은 일부 training sample과 동일한 분포를 갖는 새로운 sample을 생성하기 위한 유망한 접근법이다. 그러나 Gaussian perturbation과 같은 작은 교란에도 adversarial attack에 취약하다. 본 연구에서는 DDS를 위한 adversarial attack 및 defense 방법론의 완전한 집합을 제안한다. 공격 측면에서는 sampling 단계에 perturbation을 주입하는 방식을 제안하며, 이는 sample generation 성능을 크게 악화시킨다. 방어 측면에서는 potential function minimization을 위한 local variation 기반 regularization model을 제안하여 adversarial perturbation을 효과적으로 완화한다. 또한, 우리는 방어 모델을 풀기 위한 conjugate gradient algorithm을 개발하였으며, 이는 계산 비용을 절감하는 최근의 zeroth-order rejection sampling 방법과 통합된다. 실험 결과는 제안한 공격이 기존 state-of-the-art 방법들의 성능을 크게 악화시키지만, 제안한 local variation regularization으로 방어할 수 있음을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"61428","en":"Just Ask: Curious Code Agents Reveal System Prompts in Frontier LLMs","ko":"Just Ask: Curious Code Agents가 Frontier LLMs의 System Prompts를 드러내다","authors":"Xiang Zheng, Yutao Wu, Hanxun Huang, Yige Li, Xingjun Ma, Bo Li, Yu-Gang Jiang, Cong Wang","pos":"#4626","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=qFWLv8bLL2","abs":"<p>Autonomous code agents built on large language models are reshaping software and AI development through tool use, long-horizon reasoning, and self-directed interaction. However, this autonomy introduces a previously unrecognized security risk: agentic interaction fundamentally expands the LLM attack surface, enabling systematic probing and recovery of hidden system prompts that guide model behavior. We identify system prompt extraction as an emergent vulnerability intrinsic to code agents and present \\textbf{\\justask{}}, a self-evolving framework that autonomously discovers effective extraction strategies through interaction alone. Unlike prior prompt-engineering or dataset-based attacks, \\justask{} requires no handcrafted prompts, labeled supervision, or privileged access beyond standard user interaction. It formulates extraction as an online exploration problem, using Upper Confidence Bound--based strategy selection and a hierarchical skill space spanning atomic probes and high-level orchestration. These skills exploit imperfect system-instruction generalization and inherent tensions between helpfulness and safety. Evaluated on \\textbf{41} black-box commercial models across multiple providers, \\justask{} consistently achieves full or near-complete system prompt recovery, revealing recurring design- and architecture-level vulnerabilities. Our results expose system prompts as a critical yet largely unprotected attack surface in modern agent systems.</p>","absKo":"<p>대규모 언어 모델을 기반으로 한 자율 code agent는 tool use, long-horizon reasoning, 그리고 자기주도적 상호작용을 통해 software와 AI 개발을 재구성하고 있다. 그러나 이러한 자율성은 이전에 인식되지 않았던 보안 위험을 도입한다. agentic interaction은 LLM의 공격 표면을 근본적으로 확장하여, 모델 동작을 안내하는 hidden system prompt를 체계적으로 탐색하고 복원할 수 있게 한다. 우리는 system prompt extraction을 code agent에 내재된 emergent vulnerability로 식별하고, 상호작용만으로 효과적인 extraction 전략을 자율적으로 발견하는 self-evolving framework인 \\textbf{\\justask{}}를 제시한다. 기존의 prompt engineering이나 dataset-based attack과 달리, \\justask{}는 수작업으로 설계한 prompt, 라벨이 있는 supervision, 혹은 일반적인 사용자 상호작용을 넘어선 특권적 접근을 요구하지 않는다. 이 방법은 extraction을 online exploration problem으로 정식화하며, Upper Confidence Bound 기반 전략 선택과 atomic probe부터 고수준 orchestration까지 아우르는 hierarchical skill space를 사용한다. 이러한 skill은 불완전한 system instruction generalization과 helpfulness와 safety 사이의 내재된 긴장을 악용한다. 여러 제공업체의 \\textbf{41}개 black-box 상용 모델에서 평가한 결과, \\justask{}는 일관되게 system prompt를 완전 또는 거의 완전하게 복원하며, 반복적으로 나타나는 design- 및 architecture-level 취약점을 드러낸다. 우리의 결과는 현대 agent 시스템에서 system prompt가 중대한 공격 표면이지만 대체로 보호되지 않고 있음을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"62766","en":"Learning Unanimously Acceptable Lotteries via Queries","ko":"쿼리로 학습하는 Unanimously Acceptable Lottery","authors":"Davin Choo, Paul Goldberg, Nicholas Teh","pos":"#4617","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=daiccpXZfU","abs":"<p>Many high-stakes AI deployments proceed only if every stakeholder deems the system acceptable relative to their own minimum standard. With randomization over a finite menu of options, this becomes a feasibility question: does there exist a lottery over options that clears all stakeholders' acceptability bars? We study a query model where the algorithm proposes lotteries and receives only binary accept/reject feedback. We give deterministic and randomized algorithms that either find a unanimously acceptable lottery or certify infeasibility; adaptivity can avoid eliciting many stakeholders' constraints, and randomization further reduces the expected elicitation cost relative to full elicitation. We complement these upper bounds with worst-case lower bounds (in particular, linear dependence on the number of stakeholders and logarithmic dependence on precision are unavoidable). Finally, we develop learning-augmented algorithms that exploit natural forms of advice (e.g., likely binding stakeholders or a promising lottery), improving query complexity when predictions are accurate while preserving worst-case guarantees.</p>","absKo":"<p>많은 high-stakes AI 배포는 모든 stakeholder가 해당 system을 자신들의 최소 기준에 비추어 수용 가능하다고 판단할 때에만 진행된다. 유한한 option 집합에 대한 randomization을 허용하면 이는 feasibility question으로 바뀐다. 즉, 모든 stakeholder의 acceptability bar를 충족하는 option의 lottery가 존재하는가? 우리는 algorithm이 lottery를 제안하고 binary accept/reject feedback만 받는 query model을 연구한다. 우리는 unanimous하게 수용 가능한 lottery를 찾거나 infeasibility를 증명하는 deterministic 및 randomized algorithm을 제시한다. adaptivity는 많은 stakeholder의 제약을 모두 묻지 않고도 이를 피할 수 있으며, randomization은 full elicitation에 비해 expected elicitation cost를 추가로 줄여준다. 우리는 이러한 상한에 worst-case lower bound를 보완하는데, 특히 stakeholder 수에 대한 선형 의존성과 precision에 대한 로그 의존성은 피할 수 없다. 마지막으로, 우리는 natural한 형태의 advice(예: likely binding stakeholder 또는 유망한 lottery)를 활용하는 learning-augmented algorithm을 개발하여, 예측이 정확할 때 query complexity를 개선하면서도 worst-case 보장을 유지한다.</p>"},{"id":"63805","en":"Adaptive Contracts for Cost-Effective AI Delegation","ko":"비용 효율적 AI 위임을 위한 적응적 계약","authors":"Tamar Garbuz, Ariel Procaccia, Eden Saig, Inbal Talgam-Cohen, Jamie Tucker-Foltz","pos":"#4616","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=TZeGBqnvRT","abs":"<p>When organizations delegate text generation tasks to AI providers via pay-for-performance contracts, expected payments rise when evaluation is noisy. As evaluation methods become more elaborate, the economic benefits of decreased noise are often overshadowed by increased evaluation costs. In this work, we introduce adaptive contracts for AI delegation, which allow detailed evaluation to be performed selectively after observing an initial coarse signal in order to conserve resources. We make three sets of contributions: First, we provide efficient algorithms for computing optimal adaptive contracts under natural assumptions or when core problem dimensions are small, and prove hardness of approximation in the general unstructured case. We then formulate alternative models of randomized adaptive contracts and discuss their benefits and limitations. Finally, we empirically demonstrate the benefits of adaptivity over non-adaptive baselines using question-answering and code-generation datasets.</p>","absKo":"<p>조직이 pay-for-performance contract를 통해 AI provider에게 text generation task를 위임할 때, 평가가 noisy할수록 기대 지불액은 증가한다. 평가 방법이 더 정교해질수록 noise 감소의 경제적 이익은 종종 증가한 평가 비용에 의해 상쇄된다. 본 연구에서는 초기의 거친 signal을 관측한 뒤에만 세부 평가를 선택적으로 수행하여 자원을 절약할 수 있는 AI delegation을 위한 adaptive contract를 도입한다. 우리는 세 가지 기여를 한다. 첫째, 자연스러운 가정 하거나 핵심 문제 차원이 작을 때 optimal adaptive contract를 계산하는 효율적인 알고리즘을 제시하고, 일반적인 비구조적 경우에는 근사 어려움을 증명한다. 둘째, randomized adaptive contract의 대안적 모델을 정식화하고 그 장단점을 논의한다. 마지막으로, question-answering 및 code-generation dataset을 사용하여 non-adaptive baseline보다 adaptivity가 갖는 이점을 실증적으로 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"63952","en":"Stability beyond bounded differences: sharp generalization bounds under finite $L_p$ moments","ko":"유계 차분을 넘어: 유한 $L_p$ 모멘트 하에서의 날카로운 일반화 경계","authors":"Qianqian Lei, Soham Bonnerjee, Yuefeng Han, Wei Biao Wu","pos":"#4510","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=SGTLVjx3MN","abs":"While algorithmic stability is a central tool for understanding generalization of learning algorithms, existing high-probability guarantees typically rely on uniform boundedness or sub-Gaussian/sub-Weibull tail assumptions, which can be overly restrictive for modern settings with heavy-tailed or unbounded losses. We develop a stability-based framework that requires only a finite $L_p$ moment condition. Our first contribution is sharp concentration inequalities for functions of independent random variables under $L_p$ constraints, extending McDiarmid's bounded-differences techniques beyond the classical regime. Leveraging these results, we derive sharp high-probability generalization bounds across a range of learning paradigms, including empirical risk minimization, transductive regression, and meta-learning. These guarantees show that $L_p$ stability suffices for robust generalization even when boundedness fails, substantially weakening the standard assumptions in the stability literature.","absKo":"알고리즘 안정성은 learning algorithms의 generalization을 이해하는 데 핵심적인 도구이지만, 기존의 high-probability 보장은 대개 uniform boundedness 또는 sub-Gaussian/sub-Weibull tail 가정에 의존하며, 이는 heavy-tailed 혹은 unbounded loss를 다루는 현대적 설정에서는 지나치게 제한적일 수 있다. 우리는 finite $L_p$ moment condition만을 요구하는 stability-based framework를 개발한다. 첫 번째 기여는 $L_p$ 제약 하에서 독립 random variable의 함수에 대한 sharp concentration inequality로, McDiarmid의 bounded-differences 기법을 고전적 범위 너머로 확장한다. 이러한 결과를 활용하여 우리는 empirical risk minimization, transductive regression, meta-learning을 포함한 다양한 learning paradigm에서 sharp high-probability generalization bound를 유도한다. 이러한 보장은 boundedness가 성립하지 않더라도 $L_p$ stability만으로 robust generalization이 가능함을 보여주며, stability 문헌의 표준 가정을 크게 약화시킨다."},{"id":"63930","en":"Adaptive Preconditioners Trigger Loss Spikes in Adam","ko":"적응형 preconditioner가 Adam에서 loss spike를 유발한다","authors":"Zhiwei Bai, Zhangchen Zhou, Jiajie Zhao, Xiaolong Li, Zhiyu li, Feiyu Xiong, Hongkang Yang, Yaoyu Zhang, Zhi-Qin John Xu","pos":"#1413","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=STWQoscanw","abs":"Loss spikes commonly emerge during neural network training with the Adam optimizer across diverse architectures and scales, yet their underlying mechanism remains elusive.  While previous explanations attribute these phenomena to sharper loss landscapes at lower loss, we show that landscape geometry alone is insufficient to explain the phenomenon. In this work, we pinpoint the root cause in the internal dynamics of Adam's second moment estimator. We identify a critical ``decoupling'' mechanism where the adaptive preconditioner $v_t$ fails to track the instantaneous squared gradients $g_t^2$, causing the adaptive mechanism to effectively fail. This decoupling allows the preconditioner to decay autonomously despite rising gradients, which pushes the maximum eigenvalue of the preconditioned Hessian beyond the stability threshold $2/\\eta$ for sustained periods, manifesting as dramatic loss spikes. Through a quadratic approximation analysis, we theoretically and experimentally characterize five distinct stages of spike evolution and propose a predictor for anticipating spikes based on gradient-directional curvature. We empirically find that the proposed loss spike mechanism, although derived from simplified models, generalizes well to practical scenarios ranging from small neural networks to large-scale Transformers.","absKo":"Adam optimizer를 사용한 neural network training 중에는 다양한 architecture와 scale에서 loss spike가 흔히 나타나지만, 그 근본 메커니즘은 여전히 명확하지 않다. 이전 설명들은 낮은 loss에서 더 날카로운 loss landscape를 원인으로 지목했지만, 우리는 landscape geometry만으로는 이 현상을 설명하기에 충분하지 않음을 보인다. 본 연구에서는 Adam의 second moment estimator 내부 dynamics를 근본 원인으로 지목한다. 우리는 adaptive preconditioner $v_t$가 순간적인 squared gradient $g_t^2$를 추적하지 못하는 핵심적인 ``decoupling'' 메커니즘을 식별하며, 그 결과 adaptive mechanism이 사실상 실패하게 됨을 보인다. 이러한 decoupling은 gradient가 증가하는 동안에도 preconditioner가 자율적으로 감소하게 허용하고, 이는 preconditioned Hessian의 최대 eigenvalue를 안정성 임계값 $2/\\eta$ 이상으로 장기간 밀어 올려 극적인 loss spike로 나타난다. quadratic approximation analysis를 통해 우리는 spike evolution의 다섯 가지 distinct stage를 이론적·실험적으로 특징짓고, gradient-directional curvature를 바탕으로 spike를 예측하는 predictor를 제안한다. 실험적으로 우리는 단순화된 model에서 유도된 이 loss spike mechanism이 작은 neural network부터 대규모 Transformer에 이르는 실제 시나리오에서도 잘 일반화됨을 확인했다."},{"id":"62410","en":"Benign Overfitting in Adversarial Training for Vision Transformers","ko":"Vision Transformers의 적대적 학습에서 Benign Overfitting","authors":"Jiaming Zhang, Meng Ding, Shaopeng Fu, Jingfeng Zhang, Di Wang","pos":"#1415","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=grSvnNlEUU","abs":"<p>Despite the remarkable success of Vision Transformers (ViTs) across a wide range of vision tasks, recent studies have revealed that they remain vulnerable to adversarial examples, much like Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs). A common empirical defense strategy is adversarial training, yet the theoretical underpinnings of its robustness in ViTs remain largely unexplored. In this work, we present the first theoretical analysis of adversarial training under simplified ViT architectures. We show that, when trained under a signal-to-noise ratio that satisfies a certain condition and within a moderate perturbation budget, adversarial training enables ViTs to achieve nearly zero robust training loss and robust generalization error under certain regimes. Remarkably, this leads to strong generalization even in the presence of overfitting, a phenomenon known as \\emph{benign overfitting}, previously only observed in CNNs (with adversarial training). Experiments on both synthetic and real-world datasets further validate our theoretical findings.</p>","absKo":"<p>다양한 vision task에서 Vision Transformers (ViTs)가 거둔 놀라운 성공에도 불구하고, 최근 연구는 이들이 Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs)와 마찬가지로 adversarial example에 취약하다는 사실을 보여주었다. 흔히 사용되는 경험적 방어 전략은 adversarial training이지만, ViT에서의 robustness에 대한 이론적 토대는 여전히 대부분 탐구되지 않았다. 본 연구에서는 단순화된 ViT architecture 하에서 adversarial training에 대한 첫 이론적 분석을 제시한다. 우리는 특정 조건을 만족하는 signal-to-noise ratio와 적당한 perturbation budget 하에서 training이 이루어질 때, adversarial training이 ViT로 하여금 거의 zero에 가까운 robust training loss와 특정 regime에서의 robust generalization error를 달성하게 함을 보인다. 놀랍게도 이는 과적합이 존재하더라도 강한 generalization으로 이어지며, 이는 \\emph{benign overfitting}으로 알려진 현상으로, 이전에는 CNN에서만 adversarial training과 함께 관찰되었다. 합성 데이터셋과 실제 데이터셋 모두에서 수행한 실험은 우리의 이론적 발견을 추가로 검증한다.</p>"},{"id":"63584","en":"When Iteration Helps and Hurts in Self-Training: Denoising vs. Signal Forgetting","ko":"self-training에서 반복이 도움이 되거나 해가 되는 경우: 잡음 제거 vs. 신호 망각","authors":"Mingqi Wu, Archer Yang, Qiang Sun","pos":"#3910","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=VnA5q5jXVz","abs":"Iterative self-training (self-distillation) repeatedly refits a model on pseudo-labels generated by its own predictions. We study this procedure in overparameterized linear regression: an initial estimator is trained on noisy labels, and each subsequent iterate is trained on fresh covariates with noiseless pseudo-labels from the previous model. In the high-dimensional regime, we derive deterministic-equivalent recursions for the prediction risk and effective noise across iterations, and prove that the empirical quantities concentrate sharply around these limits. The recursion separates two competing forces: a systematic component that grows with iteration due to progressive \\emph{signal forgetting}, and a stochastic component that decays due to \\emph{denoising} via repeated data-dependent projections. Their interaction yields a $U$-shaped test-risk curve and an optimal early-stopping time. In spiked covariance models, iteration further acts as an iteration-dependent spectral filter that preserves strong eigendirections while suppressing weaker ones, inducing an implicit form of soft feature selection distinct from ridge regression. Finally, we propose an \\emph{iterated} generalized cross-validation criterion and prove its uniform consistency for estimating the risk along the self-training trajectory, enabling fully data-driven selection of the stopping time and regularization. Experiments on synthetic covariances validate the theory and illustrate the predicted denoising–forgetting trade-off.","absKo":"Iterative self-training(self-distillation)은 모델이 자신의 prediction으로 생성한 pseudo-label에 대해 반복적으로 다시 적합하는 방법이다. 우리는 과매개변수 선형 회귀에서 이 절차를 연구한다. 초기 estimator는 noisy label로 학습되고, 이후 각 iterate는 이전 model의 noiseless pseudo-label을 사용해 새로운 covariate 위에서 학습된다. 고차원 regime에서, 우리는 iteration 전반에 걸친 prediction risk와 effective noise에 대한 deterministic-equivalent recursion을 유도하고, empirical quantity가 이러한 limit 주변으로 날카롭게 집중함을 증명한다. 이 recursion은 두 가지 경쟁하는 힘을 분리한다. 하나는 progressive \\emph{signal forgetting}으로 인해 iteration이 진행될수록 커지는 체계적 성분이고, 다른 하나는 반복된 data-dependent projection을 통한 \\emph{denoising}으로 인해 감소하는 stochastic 성분이다. 이들의 상호작용은 $U$자형 test-risk curve와 최적의 early-stopping time을 만들어낸다. spiked covariance model에서는 iteration이 iteration-dependent spectral filter로도 작동하여 강한 eigendirection은 보존하고 약한 eigendirection은 억제함으로써, ridge regression과 구별되는 soft feature selection의 암묵적 형태를 유도한다. 마지막으로, 우리는 \\emph{iterated} generalized cross-validation criterion을 제안하고 self-training trajectory를 따라 risk를 추정하는 데 대한 uniform consistency를 증명함으로써, stopping time과 regularization의 완전한 data-driven 선택을 가능하게 한다. synthetic covariance에서의 실험은 이 이론을 검증하고, 예측된 denoising–forgetting trade-off를 보여준다."},{"id":"65481","en":"Trajectory Seriation via Spectral Tangent Alignment and Global Embedding","ko":"스펙트럼 접선 정렬 및 전역 임베딩을 통한 궤적 순서화","authors":"Zhixin Zhou, Navin Souda, Arash Amini","pos":"#4000","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=DDNQOnaRQk","abs":"<p>This paper addresses the problem of linear seriation: recovering the intrinsic order of noisy samples drawn from an unknown one-dimensional manifold embedded in a higher-dimensional space. We propose a multi-stage approach that first robustly estimates local tangent directions using Principal Component Analysis (PCA) on neighborhoods, establishing theoretical consistency for these local estimates. Global orientation consistency of these tangents is then achieved through a spectral relaxation of a pairwise alignment objective. Finally, a globally consistent 1D embedding is computed by solving a carefully formulated linear system (or equivalently, a spectral problem on a derived Laplacian) that aligns the embedding with the oriented local projections. This method effectively leverages local geometric information while ensuring global coherence, producing an ordering robust to noise, curvature, and initial data rotation. We demonstrate its performance on simulated manifold data and discuss the theoretical underpinnings of its core components.</p>"},{"id":"71801","en":"Statistical-Computational Trade-offs for Recursive Adaptive Partitioning Estimators","ko":"재귀적 적응 분할 추정기의 통계-계산 트레이드오프","authors":"Yan Shuo Tan, Jason Klusowski, Krishnakumar Balasubramanian","pos":"#4212","abs":"<p>Models based on recursive adaptive partitioning such as decision trees and their ensembles are popular for high-dimensional regression as they can potentially avoid the curse of dimensionality. Because empirical risk minimization (ERM) is computationally infeasible, these models are typically trained using greedy algorithms. Although effective in many cases, these algorithms have been empirically observed to get stuck at local optima. We explore this phenomenon in the context of learning sparse regression functions over d binary features, showing that when the true regression function f? does not satisfy Abbe et al. (2022)'s Merged Staircase Property (MSP), greedy training requires exp(?(d)) to achieve low estimation error. Conversely, when f? does satisfy MSP, greedy training can attain small estimation error with only O(logd) samples. This dichotomy mirrors that of two-layer neural networks trained with stochastic gradient descent (SGD) in the mean-field regime, thereby establishing a head-to-head comparison between SGD-trained neural networks and greedy recursive partitioning estimators. Furthermore, ERM-trained recursive partitioning estimators achieve low estimation error with O(logd) samples irrespective of whether f? satisfies MSP, thereby demonstrating a statistical-computational trade-off for greedy training. Our proofs are based on a novel interpretation of greedy recursive partitioning using stochastic process theory and a coupling technique that may be of independent interest.</p>"},{"id":"61730","en":"Convex Distance Operator Transport: Convex and Geometry-Preserving Information","ko":"Convex Distance Operator Transport: Convex하고 기하를 보존하는 정보","authors":"Junhyoung Chung, Euijong Song, Won Hwa Kim, Gunwoong Park","pos":"#4302","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=nPC7M7XLEv","abs":"<p>We introduce Convex Distance Operator Transport (CDOT), the first convex optimal transport framework that aligns distributions across heterogeneous domains by jointly preserving feature correspondence and intrinsic geometric structure. Specifically, CDOT employs an operator-based regularization that aligns aggregated distance structures by introducing distance and conditional expectation operators. Consequently, the proposed regularization improves the robustness to local geometric variations. We further prove that the resulting CDOT discrepancy is a valid pseudometric on the space of attributed compact metric-measure spaces. In addition, we characterize the relationship between CDOT and Gromov--Wasserstien (GW) through a new notion of dispersion gap, formally elucidating the geometric source of non-convexity in GW compared to the convexity of CDOT. In the finite-sample regime, we derive a non-asymptotic risk bound decomposed into optimization and statistical errors, establishing risk consistency under a globally convergent Frank--Wolfe algorithm. Experiments on synthetic point clouds, brain connectomes, and graph classification benchmarks demonstrate better performance over existing methods, with stable and reliable behavior in practice.</p>","absKo":"<p>우리는 서로 다른 domain 간 분포를 정렬하면서 feature correspondence와 intrinsic geometric structure를 함께 보존하는, 최초의 convex optimal transport framework인 Convex Distance Operator Transport (CDOT)를 소개합니다. 구체적으로 CDOT는 distance operator와 conditional expectation operator를 도입하여 aggregated distance structure를 정렬하는 operator-based regularization을 사용합니다. 그 결과 제안된 regularization은 local geometric variation에 대한 robustness를 향상시킵니다. 또한 결과적으로 얻어지는 CDOT discrepancy가 attributed compact metric-measure space 위의 valid pseudometric임을 증명합니다. 더 나아가, 우리는 dispersion gap이라는 새로운 개념을 통해 CDOT와 Gromov--Wasserstien (GW) 사이의 관계를 규정하고, GW의 비볼록성에 대한 기하학적 근원을 CDOT의 볼록성과 대비하여 형식적으로 설명합니다. finite-sample regime에서는 optimization error와 statistical error로 분해되는 non-asymptotic risk bound를 유도하고, globally convergent Frank--Wolfe algorithm 하에서 risk consistency를 확립합니다. synthetic point cloud, brain connectome, graph classification benchmark 실험은 기존 방법보다 더 나은 성능과, 실제 적용에서의 안정적이고 신뢰할 수 있는 동작을 보여줍니다.</p>"},{"id":"71804","en":"Meta-Learning with Generalized Ridge Regression: High-dimensional Asymptotics, Optimality and Hyper-covariance Estimation","ko":"일반화된 Ridge Regression을 이용한 Meta-Learning: 고차원 점근, 최적성 및 Hyper-covariance 추정","authors":"Yanhao Jin, Krishna Balasubramanian, Debashis Paul","pos":"#4400","abs":"<p>Meta-learning involves training models on a variety of training tasks in a way that enables them to generalize well on new, unseen test tasks. In this work, we consider meta-learning within the framework of high-dimensional multivariate random-effects linear models and study generalized ridge-regression based predictions. The statistical intuition of using generalized ridge regression in this setting is that the covariance structure of the random regression coefficients could be leveraged to make better predictions on new tasks. Accordingly, we first characterize the precise asymptotic behavior of the predictive risk for a new test task when the data dimension grows proportionally to the number of samples per task. We next show that this predictive risk is optimal when the weight matrix in generalized ridge regression is chosen to be the inverse of the covariance matrix of random coefficients. Finally, we propose and analyze an estimator of the inverse covariance matrix of random regression coefficients based on data from the training tasks. As opposed to intractable MLE-type estimators, the proposed estimators could be computed efficiently as they could be obtained by solving (global) geodesically-convex optimization problems. Our analysis and methodology use tools from random matrix theory and Riemannian optimization. Simulation results demonstrate the improved generalization performance of the proposed method on new unseen test tasks within the considered framework.</p>"},{"id":"65217","en":"Outcome-Aware Spectral Feature Learning for Instrumental Variable Regression","ko":"도구 변수 회귀를 위한 결과 인지 스펙트럼 특징 학습","authors":"Dimitri Meunier, Jakub Wornbard, Vladimir Kostic, Antoine Moulin, Alek Fröhlich, Karim Lounici, Massimiliano Pontil, Arthur Gretton","pos":"#4413","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=FiCxlfjkhc","abs":"<p>We address the problem of causal effect estimation in the presence of hidden confounders using nonparametric instrumental variable (IV) regression. An established approach is to use estimators based on learned \\emph{spectral features}, that is, features spanning the top singular subspaces of the operator linking treatments to instruments. While powerful, such features are agnostic to the outcome variable. Consequently, the method can fail when the true causal function is poorly represented by these dominant singular functions.  To mitigate, we introduce Augmented Spectral Feature Learning, a framework that makes the feature learning process outcome-aware. Our method learns features by minimizing a novel contrastive loss derived from an augmented operator that incorporates information from the outcome. By learning these task-specific features, our approach remains effective even under spectral misalignment. We provide a theoretical analysis of this framework and validate our approach on challenging benchmarks.</p>"},{"id":"61057","en":"Flat Minima and Generalization: Insights from Stochastic Convex Optimization","ko":"평탄한 Minima와 일반화: Stochastic Convex Optimization에서의 통찰","authors":"Matan Schliserman, Shira Vansover-Hager, Tomer Koren","pos":"#4506","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=u6zp8zZ8Ou","abs":"Understanding the generalization behavior of learning algorithms is a central goal of learning theory. A recently emerging explanation is that learning algorithms are successful in practice because they converge to flat minima, which have been consistently associated with improved generalization performance.  In this work, we study the link between flat minima and generalization in the canonical setting of stochastic convex optimization with a non-negative, $\\beta$-smooth objective. Our first finding is that, even in this fundamental setting, flat empirical minima may incur trivial $\\Omega(1)$ population risk while sharp minima generalizes optimally. We then demonstrate that this phenomenon extends to sharpness-aware algorithms introduced by Foret et al. (2021), namely Sharpness-Aware Gradient Descent (SA-GD) and Sharpness-Aware Minimization (SAM). For SA-GD we prove that it successfully converges to a flat minimum at a fast rate, but the population risk of the solution can still be as large as $\\Omega(1)$. For SAM we show that although it minimizes the empirical loss, it may converge to a sharp minimum and also incur population risk $\\Omega(1)$.  Finally, we establish population risk upper bounds for both SA-GD and SAM using algorithmic stability techniques.","absKo":"학습 알고리즘의 generalization behavior를 이해하는 것은 learning theory의 핵심 목표이다. 최근 등장한 설명 중 하나는, 학습 알고리즘이 flat minima로 수렴하기 때문에 실제 성능이 좋다는 것이다. flat minima는 일반화 성능 향상과 일관되게 연관되어 왔다. 본 연구에서는 비음이 아닌 $\\beta$-smooth objective를 갖는 stochastic convex optimization의 전형적 설정에서 flat minima와 generalization 사이의 관계를 연구한다. 우리의 첫 번째 결과는, 이 근본적인 설정에서도 flat empirical minima가 trivial한 $\\Omega(1)$ population risk를 가질 수 있는 반면, sharp minima는 최적으로 generalize된다는 것이다. 이어서 우리는 이 현상이 Foret et al. (2021)이 도입한 sharpness-aware 알고리즘, 즉 Sharpness-Aware Gradient Descent (SA-GD)와 Sharpness-Aware Minimization (SAM)으로도 확장됨을 보인다. SA-GD에 대해서는 빠른 속도로 flat minimum에 성공적으로 수렴함을 증명하지만, 해의 population risk는 여전히 $\\Omega(1)$까지 커질 수 있다. SAM에 대해서는 empirical loss를 최소화하지만 sharp minimum으로 수렴할 수 있으며, 역시 population risk $\\Omega(1)$를 초래할 수 있음을 보인다. 마지막으로, algorithmic stability 기법을 사용해 SA-GD와 SAM 모두에 대한 population risk 상한을 제시한다."},{"id":"60677","en":"Statistical Consistency and Generalization of Contrastive Representation Learning","ko":"Contrastive Representation Learning의 통계적 일관성과 일반화","authors":"Yuanfan Li, Xiyuan Wei, Tianbao Yang, Yiming Ying","pos":"#4509","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=xixoixLXCr","abs":"Contrastive representation learning (CRL) underpins many modern foundation models. Despite recent theoretical progress, existing analyses suffer from several key limitations: (i) the statistical consistency of CRL remains poorly understood; (ii) available generalization bounds deteriorate as the number of negative samples increases, contradicting the empirical benefits of large negative sets; and (iii) the retrieval performance of CRL has received limited theoretical attention.  In this paper, we develop a unified statistical learning theory for CRL. For downstream tasks, we evaluate retrieval quality using an AUC-type population criterion and show that the contrastive loss is *statistically consistent* with optimal ranking. We further establish a *calibration-style inequality* that quantitatively relates excess contrastive risk to excess retrieval suboptimality. For upstream training, we study both supervised and self-supervised contrastive objectives and derive generalization bounds of order $O(1/m + 1/\\sqrt{n})$ and $O(1/\\sqrt{m} + 1/\\sqrt{n})$, respectively, where $m$ denotes the number of negative samples and $n$ the number of anchor points. These bounds not only explain the empirical advantages of large negative sets but also reveal an explicit trade-off between $m$ and $n$. Extensive experiments on large-scale vision--language models corroborate our theoretical predictions.","absKo":"Contrastive representation learning (CRL)은 많은 현대 foundation model의 기반이 된다. 최근 이론적 진전에도 불구하고, 기존 분석에는 몇 가지 중요한 한계가 있다: (i) CRL의 statistical consistency는 여전히 충분히 이해되지 않았고; (ii) 사용 가능한 generalization bound는 negative sample 수가 증가할수록 악화되며, 이는 큰 negative set의 경험적 이점과 모순되고; (iii) CRL의 retrieval performance에 대해서는 이론적 관심이 제한적이었다. 본 논문에서는 CRL을 위한 통합된 statistical learning theory를 개발한다. downstream task에 대해서는 AUC-type population criterion을 사용해 retrieval quality를 평가하고, contrastive loss가 optimal ranking과 *statistically consistent*하다는 것을 보인다. 또한 excess contrastive risk와 excess retrieval suboptimality를 정량적으로 연결하는 *calibration-style inequality*를 확립한다. upstream training에 대해서는 supervised 및 self-supervised contrastive objective를 모두 다루고, 각각 $O(1/m + 1/\\sqrt{n})$ 및 $O(1/\\sqrt{m} + 1/\\sqrt{n})$ 차수의 generalization bound를 도출한다. 여기서 $m$은 negative sample 수, $n$은 anchor point 수를 뜻한다. 이러한 bound는 큰 negative set의 경험적 이점을 설명할 뿐 아니라 $m$과 $n$ 사이의 명시적인 trade-off도 드러낸다. 대규모 vision--language model에 대한 광범위한 실험은 우리의 이론적 예측을 뒷받침한다."},{"id":"62156","en":"Stability and Generalization of Nonconvex Optimization with Heavy-Tailed Noise","ko":"Heavy-Tailed Noise가 있는 비볼록 최적화의 안정성과 일반화","authors":"Hongxu Chen, Ke Wei, Xiaoming Yuan, Luo Luo","pos":"#4511","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=jHUEoBLQpn","abs":"The empirical evidence indicates that stochastic optimization with heavy-tailed gradient noise is more appropriate to characterize the training of machine learning models than that with standard bounded gradient variance noise. Most existing works on this phenomenon focus on the  convergence of optimization errors, while the analysis for generalization bounds under the heavy-tailed gradient noise remains limited. In this paper, we develop a general framework for establishing generalization bounds under heavy-tailed noise. Specifically, we introduce a truncation argument to achieve the generalization error bound based on the algorithmic stability under the assumption of bounded $p$th centered moment with $p\\in(1,2]$. Building on this framework, we further provide the stability and generalization analysis for several popular stochastic algorithms under heavy-tailed noise, including clipped and normalized stochastic gradient descent, as well as their mini-batch and momentum variants.","absKo":"실증적 증거는 heavy-tailed gradient noise를 갖는 stochastic optimization이, 표준 bounded gradient variance noise보다 machine learning model의 training을 설명하는 데 더 적절함을 시사한다. 이 현상에 관한 대부분의 기존 연구는 optimization error의 convergence에 초점을 맞추는 반면, heavy-tailed gradient noise 하에서의 generalization bound 분석은 여전히 제한적이다. 이 논문에서는 heavy-tailed noise 하에서 generalization bound를 확립하기 위한 일반적인 framework를 개발한다. 구체적으로, $p\\in(1,2]$인 bounded $p$th centered moment 가정하에서 algorithmic stability를 기반으로 generalization error bound를 얻기 위해 truncation argument를 도입한다. 이 framework를 바탕으로, 우리는 clipped 및 normalized stochastic gradient descent와 그 mini-batch 및 momentum variant를 포함한 여러 인기 있는 stochastic algorithm에 대해 heavy-tailed noise 하의 stability 및 generalization 분석을 추가로 제시한다."},{"id":"62429","en":"Sharper Generalization Guarantees for Asynchronous SGD: Beyond Lipschitzness, Smoothness and Data Homogeneity","ko":"비동기 SGD의 일반화 보장 강화: Lipschitzness, Smoothness, 데이터 동질성 조건을 넘어","authors":"Yufeng Xie, Yunwen Lei","pos":"#4512","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=giCCyIbMHc","abs":"Asynchronous stochastic gradient descent (ASGD) is widely adopted in distributed and federated learning. In this paper, we develop a sharp generalization analysis for ASGD by leveraging the concept of on-average model stability. For convex and smooth objectives, we establish stability and excess risk bounds under minimal assumptions, removing Lipschitz continuity, bounded noise, bounded parameter or data domains, while allowing randomly partitioned data and arbitrary delays. Our bounds are optimistic and explicitly characterize the impact of worker participation, recovering the minimax-optimal rate $O(1/\\sqrt{mn})$ in balanced regimes where $mn$ denotes the sample size and implying fast rates under low-noise conditions. We further extend the analysis to non-smooth objectives with Hölder-continuous gradients and to heterogeneous data settings via random ASGD, obtaining  non-vacuous excess risk guarantees in both settings. Experimental results support our theoretical findings.","absKo":"Asynchronous stochastic gradient descent (ASGD)는 distributed learning과 federated learning에서 널리 채택된다. 본 논문에서는 on-average model stability 개념을 활용하여 ASGD에 대한 날카로운 generalization analysis를 전개한다. convex하고 smooth한 objective에 대해, 우리는 Lipschitz continuity, bounded noise, bounded parameter 또는 data domain을 제거하고 randomly partitioned data와 arbitrary delay를 허용하는 최소 가정하에서 stability 및 excess risk bound를 확립한다. 우리의 bound는 optimistic하며 worker 참여의 영향을 명시적으로 특성화하고, 균형 잡힌 regime에서 sample size를 $mn$으로 둘 때 minimax-optimal rate $O(1/\\sqrt{mn})$를 회복하며, low-noise condition에서는 fast rate를 함의한다. 우리는 또한 Hölder-continuous gradient를 갖는 non-smooth objective와 random ASGD를 통한 heterogeneous data setting으로 분석을 확장하여, 두 설정 모두에서 non-vacuous excess risk guarantee를 얻는다. 실험 결과는 이론적 발견을 뒷받침한다."},{"id":"64582","en":"Scaling Laws for Precision in High-Dimensional Linear Regression","ko":"고차원 선형 회귀에서 정밀도에 대한 Scaling Law","authors":"Dechen Zhang, Xuan Tang, Yingyu Liang, Difan Zou","pos":"#4513","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=LyhBIrNBXv","abs":"<p>Low-precision training is critical for optimizing the trade-off between model quality and training costs, necessitating the joint allocation of model size, dataset size, and numerical precision. While empirical scaling laws suggest that quantization impacts effective model and data capacities or acts as an additive error, the theoretical mechanisms governing these effects remain largely unexplored. In this work, we initiate a theoretical study of scaling laws for low-precision training within a high-dimensional sketched linear regression framework. We demonstrate that the impact of quantization is twofold: it introduces an additive error and, simultaneously, shrinks the effective model and data sizes. Crucially, our analysis reveals distinct behaviors across quantization regimes: multiplicative quantization (where error variance scales with signal magnitude) primarily reduces the effective data size, whereas additive quantization (where error variance is independent of the signal) diminishes both the effective model size and data size. Numerical experiments validate our theoretical findings. By rigorously characterizing the complex interplay among model scale, dataset size, and quantization error, our work provides a principled theoretical basis for optimizing training protocols under practical hardware constraints.</p>","absKo":"<p>Low-precision training은 model quality와 training cost 사이의 trade-off를 최적화하는 데 핵심적이며, model size, dataset size, numerical precision의 공동 할당을 필요로 한다. 실증적 scaling law는 quantization이 effective model 및 data capacity에 영향을 주거나 additive error로 작용함을 시사하지만, 이러한 효과를 지배하는 이론적 메커니즘은 아직 충분히 탐구되지 않았다. 본 연구에서는 high-dimensional sketched linear regression framework에서 low-precision training을 위한 scaling law의 이론적 연구를 시작한다. 우리는 quantization의 영향이 이중적임을 보인다. 즉, additive error를 도입하는 동시에 effective model size와 data size를 함께 축소한다. 특히 우리의 분석은 quantization regime에 따라 서로 다른 동작을 드러낸다. multiplicative quantization(오차 분산이 signal magnitude에 따라 스케일됨)은 주로 effective data size를 감소시키는 반면, additive quantization(오차 분산이 signal과 무관함)은 effective model size와 data size를 모두 감소시킨다. 수치 실험은 우리의 이론적 결과를 검증한다. model scale, dataset size, quantization error 간의 복잡한 상호작용을 엄밀하게 특성화함으로써, 본 연구는 실제 hardware 제약 하에서 training protocol을 최적화하기 위한 원리 기반의 이론적 토대를 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"64134","en":"SAQNN: Spectral Adaptive Quantum Neural Network as a Universal Approximator","ko":"SAQNN: 범용 근사자로서의 스펙트럼 적응 양자 신경망","authors":"Jialiang Tang, Jialin Zhang, Xiaoming Sun","pos":"#4515","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=QaHFVheV8X","abs":"Quantum machine learning (QML), as an interdisciplinary field bridging quantum computing and machine learning, has garnered significant attention in recent years. Currently, the field as a whole faces challenges due to incomplete theoretical foundations for the expressivity of quantum neural networks (QNNs). In this paper we propose a constructive QNN model and demonstrate that it possesses the universal approximation property (UAP), which means it can approximate any square-integrable function up to arbitrary accuracy. Furthermore, it supports switching function bases, thus adaptable to various scenarios in numerical approximation and machine learning. Our model has asymptotic advantages over the best classical feed-forward neural networks in terms of circuit size and achieves optimal parameter complexity when approximating Sobolev functions under $L_2$ norm.","absKo":"Quantum machine learning (QML)은 quantum computing과 machine learning을 잇는 학제 간 분야로서 최근 몇 년간 큰 주목을 받아왔다. 현재 이 분야는 quantum neural network (QNN)의 expressivity에 대한 이론적 기반이 불완전하여 전반적으로 어려움을 겪고 있다. 본 논문에서는 constructive QNN model을 제안하고, 이것이 universal approximation property (UAP)를 가진다는 것을 보인다. 이는 임의의 정확도로 어떤 square-integrable function도 근사할 수 있음을 의미한다. 더 나아가, 이 모델은 switching function basis를 지원하므로 수치 근사와 machine learning의 다양한 상황에 유연하게 적용될 수 있다. 우리의 모델은 circuit size 측면에서 최선의 classical feed-forward neural network보다 asymptotic advantage를 가지며, $L_2$ norm 하에서 Sobolev function을 근사할 때 최적의 parameter complexity를 달성한다."},{"id":"65796","en":"Provably Label-Efficient Conformal Prediction","ko":"증명 가능하게 레이블 효율적인 Conformal 예측","authors":"Andrew Ilyas, Joonhyuk Ko, Jingwu Tang, Steven Wu, Jiahao Zhang","pos":"#4516","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=A3HTrOhVnD","abs":"Conformal prediction converts any black-box predictor into one with finite-sample, distribution-free coverage guarantees, outputting prediction sets $T(x)$ that contain the true label with probability at least $1-\\alpha$. To construct these prediction sets, conformal prediction relies on a randomly sampled ``calibration set'' of labeled examples. In many applications, however, this labeled calibration set is costly to collect, creating a tradeoff between upfront labeling cost and downstream utility of the conformal predictor. In this work, we study *conformal prediction with costly label queries*, where unlabeled examples arrive i.i.d. and labels can be queried one at a time. After $m$ queries, we form a conformal predictor; the upfront cost of this predictor is the calibration set size $m$, and its efficiency is the expected prediction set size $\\mathbb{E}|T_m(X)|$. We design an online stopping rule $\\hat{m}$ that automatically balances the upfront cost against conformal efficiency *while preserving the original conformal guarantee*. Theoretically, we show that under mild regularity assumptions, the expected total cost of our stopping rule matches the best fixed calibration size in hindsight. Experimentally, we find that our stopping rule reduces cost compared to standard choices of $m$ from the literature by 41.4% $\\pm$ 2.3%. Finally, as a concrete application we demonstrate a reduction from CP to the probably approximately correct labeling problem of Candès et al. (2025), under which our stopping rule minimizes the total labeling cost."},{"id":"66441","en":"Efficient and Minimax-optimal In-context Nonparametric Regression with Transformers","ko":"Transformer를 이용한 효율적이고 최소최대 최적인 In-context 비모수 회귀","authors":"Michelle Ching, Ioana Popescu, Nico Smith, Tianyi Ma, William Underwood, Richard Samworth","pos":"#4608","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=3hD1gzThtY","abs":"We study in-context learning for nonparametric regression with $\\alpha$-Hölder smooth regression functions, for some $\\alpha&gt;0$. We prove that, with $n$ in-context examples and $d$-dimensional regression covariates, a pretrained transformer with $\\Theta(\\log n)$ parameters and $\\Omega\\bigl(n^{2\\alpha/(2\\alpha+d)}\\log^3 n\\bigr)$ pretraining sequences can achieve the minimax-optimal rate of convergence $O\\bigl(n^{-2\\alpha/(2\\alpha+d)}\\bigr)$ in mean squared error. Our result requires substantially fewer transformer parameters and pretraining sequences than previous results in the literature. This is achieved by showing that transformers are able to approximate local polynomial estimators efficiently by implementing a kernel-weighted polynomial basis and then running gradient descent."},{"id":"71802","en":"Precise Asymptotics of Bagging Regularized M-estimators","ko":"Bagging된 Regularized M-estimator의 정밀 점근","authors":"Takuya Koriyama, Pratik Patil, Jin-Hong Du, Kai Tan, Pierre C Bellec","pos":"#4615","abs":"<p>We characterize the squared prediction risk of ensemble estimators obtained through subagging (subsample bootstrap aggregating) regularized M-estimators and construct a consistent estimator for the risk. Specifically, we consider a heterogeneous collection of M?1 regularized M-estimators, each trained with (possibly different) subsample sizes, convex differentiable losses, and convex regularizers. We operate under the proportional asymptotics regime, where the sample size n, feature size p, and subsample sizes km for m?[M] all diverge with fixed limiting ratios n/p and km/n. Key to our analysis is a new result on the joint asymptotic behavior of correlations between the estimator and residual errors on overlapping subsamples, governed through a (provably) contractive nonlinear system of equations. Of independent interest, we also establish convergence of trace functionals related to degrees of freedom in the non-ensemble setting (with M=1) along the way, extending previously known cases for squared loss with ridge and lasso regularizers. When specialized to homogeneous ensembles trained with a common loss, regularizer, and subsample size, the risk characterization sheds some light on the implicit regularization effect due to the ensemble and subsample sizes (M,k). For any ensemble size M, optimally tuning subsample size yields sample-wise monotonic risk. For the full-ensemble estimator (when M??), the optimal subsample size k? tends to be in the overparameterized regime (k??min{n,p}), when explicit regularization is vanishing. Finally, joint optimization of subsample size, ensemble size, and regularization can significantly outperform regularizer optimization alone on the full data (without any subagging).</p>"},{"id":"66370","en":"Alignment-Sensitive Minimax Rates for Spectral Algorithms with Learned Kernels","ko":"학습된 커널을 갖는 스펙트럼 알고리즘의 정렬 민감 최소최대 비율","authors":"Dongming Huang, Zhifan Li, Yicheng Li, Qian Lin","pos":"#4618","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=4HrWo5x7YF","abs":"We study spectral algorithms in the setting where kernels are learned from data. We introduce the effective span dimension (ESD), an alignment-sensitive complexity measure that depends jointly on the signal, spectrum, and noise level $\\sigma^2$. The ESD is well-defined for arbitrary kernels and signals without requiring eigen-decay conditions or source conditions. We prove that for sequence models whose ESD is at most $K$, the minimax excess risk scales as $\\sigma^2 K$. Furthermore, we analyze overparameterized gradient flow and prove that it can reduce the ESD of a sequence model, which in turn moves the problem into an easier ESD class and lowers the corresponding minimax risk. This analysis suggests a general route to study how adaptive feature learning can improve generalization through signal-kernel alignment: adaptive learning procedures reshape the kernel so that the ESD decreases and the problem enters an easier ESD class. We also extend the ESD framework to linear models and RKHS regression, and we support the theory with numerical experiments. This framework provides a novel perspective on generalization beyond traditional fixed-kernel theories."},{"id":"64579","en":"All ERMs Can Fail in Stochastic Convex Optimization Lower Bounds in Linear Dimension","ko":"모든 ERM은 실패할 수 있다: 선형 차원에서의 Stochastic Convex Optimization 하한","authors":"Tal Burla, Roi Livni","pos":"#4619","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Lzwp2KXedc","abs":"We study the sample complexity of *best-case* Empirical Risk Minimizer in the setting of Stochastic Convex Optimization. We show that there exists an instance, where sample size is linear in dimension, learning is possible, but an Empirical Risk Minimizer is likely to be *unique* and *overfits*. This resolves an open question by Feldman. We also extend this to approximate ERMs.  Building on our construction we also show that (constrained) Gradient Descent potentially overfits when horizon and learning rate grow w.r.t sample size. Specifically we provide a novel generalization lower bound of $\\Omega\\left(\\eta T/(m\\sqrt{m})\\right)$ for Gradient Descent, where $\\eta$ is the learning rate, $T$ is the horizon and $m$ is the sample size. This narrows down, exponentially, the gap between the best known upper bound of $O(\\eta T/m)$ and existing lower bounds from previous constructions.","absKo":"우리는 Stochastic Convex Optimization 설정에서 *best-case* Empirical Risk Minimizer의 sample complexity를 연구한다. 우리는 sample size가 dimension에 대해 선형일 때 학습은 가능하지만, Empirical Risk Minimizer가 *unique*하고 *overfit*하기 쉬운 인스턴스가 존재함을 보인다. 이는 Feldman의 열린 문제를 해결한다. 또한 이를 approximate ERM으로 확장한다. 우리의 구성에 기반하여, horizon과 learning rate가 sample size에 따라 증가할 때 (constrained) Gradient Descent가 과적합할 가능성도 보인다. 구체적으로, Gradient Descent에 대해 $\\Omega\\left(\\eta T/(m\\sqrt{m})\\right)$의 새로운 generalization lower bound를 제시하는데, 여기서 $\\eta$는 learning rate, $T$는 horizon, $m$은 sample size이다. 이는 기존 구성들로부터의 기존 lower bound와 best known upper bound인 $O(\\eta T/m)$ 사이의 간극을 지수적으로 좁힌다."},{"id":"61835","en":"Approximation Error Upper and Lower Bounds  for Hölder Class with Transformers","ko":"Transformer를 사용한 Hölder Class의 근사 오차 상한 및 하한","authors":"Xin He, Yuling Jiao, Xiliang Lu, Jerry Yang","pos":"#4620","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=mWBxEAq9lv","abs":"We explore the expressive power of Transformers by establishing precise approximation error upper and lower bounds for Hölder class. Specifically, a new approximation upper bound is derived for the standard Transformer architecture equipped with Softmax operators, ReLU activation functions, and residual connections. We prove that a Transformer network composed of at most $\\mathcal{O}(\\varepsilon^{-{d_{0}}/{\\alpha}})$ blocks can approximate any bounded Hölder function with $d_{0}$-dimensional input and smoothness $\\alpha\\in(0,1]$ under any accuracy $\\varepsilon&gt;0$. In the case of approximation lower bounds, leveraging the VC-dimension upper bound, we are the first to rigorously prove that Transformers demand for at least $\\mathcal{O}(\\varepsilon^{-{d_{0}}/({4\\alpha})})$ blocks to achieve the $\\varepsilon$ approximation accuracy. As a final step, we extend the derived results for standard Transformers to a general regression task and establish the corresponding excess risk rates demonstrating Transformers' empirical effectiveness in real-world settings.","absKo":"우리는 Hölder class에 대해 정확한 approximation error의 상한과 하한을 확립함으로써 Transformers의 expressive power를 탐구한다. 구체적으로, Softmax operators, ReLU activation functions, 그리고 residual connections를 갖춘 표준 Transformer architecture에 대해 새로운 approximation upper bound를 유도한다. 우리는 최대 $\\mathcal{O}(\\varepsilon^{-{d_{0}}/{\\alpha}})$개의 block으로 구성된 Transformer network가, $d_{0}$차원 input과 smoothness $\\alpha\\in(0,1]$을 갖는 임의의 bounded Hölder function을, 정확도 $\\varepsilon&gt;0$ 하에서 근사할 수 있음을 증명한다. approximation lower bounds의 경우에는 VC-dimension upper bound를 활용하여, Transformers가 $\\varepsilon$ approximation accuracy를 달성하기 위해 최소 $\\mathcal{O}(\\varepsilon^{-{d_{0}}/({4\\alpha})})$개의 block을 필요로 한다는 것을 우리가 최초로 엄밀하게 증명한다. 마지막 단계로, 도출한 표준 Transformers에 대한 결과를 일반 regression task로 확장하고, 실제 세계 설정에서 Transformers의 경험적 효과를 보여주는 corresponding excess risk rates를 확립한다."},{"id":"61097","en":"Continuous Variable Hamiltonian Learning at Heisenberg Limit via Displacement-Random Unitary Transformation","ko":"Displacement-Random Unitary Transformation을 통한 Heisenberg 한계의 Continuous Variable Hamiltonian Learning","authors":"Xi Huang, Lixing Zhang, Di Luo","pos":"#4621","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=tiF3tA5pau","abs":"<p>Characterizing the Hamiltonians of continuous-variable (CV) quantum systems remains a fundamental challenge due to the infinite-dimensional Hilbert space and the presence of unbounded operators. Existing learning protocols are often restricted to low-order Hamiltonian structures and can be sensitive to experimental noise, leaving generic multi-mode settings largely unresolved. In this work, we introduce the Displacement-Random Unitary Transformation (D-RUT), an experimentally accessible protocol for learning the coefficients of generic multi-mode bosonic Hamiltonians of arbitrary finite order. We prove that D-RUT achieves Heisenberg-limited scaling while remaining robust to state preparation and measurement (SPAM) errors. To extend the method efficiently to multi-mode systems, we develop a hierarchical coefficient recovery strategy that yields superior statistical efficiency compared to existing simultaneous estimation schemes. Importantly, we further show that our framework applies naturally to Hamiltonian coefficient learning in the first-quantized formulations, substantially broadening its scope beyond prior CV approaches. Numerical experiments validate the predicted Heisenberg scaling our approach in both single- and multi-mode nonlinear systems.</p>","absKo":"<p>continuous-variable (CV) quantum system의 Hamiltonian을 특성화하는 일은 infinite-dimensional Hilbert space와 unbounded operator의 존재 때문에 여전히 근본적인 도전 과제이다. 기존 learning protocol은 대개 low-order Hamiltonian 구조에 제한되며 실험 잡음에 민감할 수 있어, 일반적인 multi-mode setting은 여전히 충분히 해결되지 않았다. 본 연구에서는 임의의 유한 차수를 갖는 일반적인 multi-mode bosonic Hamiltonian의 계수를 학습하기 위한 실험적으로 접근 가능한 protocol인 Displacement-Random Unitary Transformation (D-RUT)을 소개한다. 우리는 D-RUT가 state preparation and measurement (SPAM) error에 강건하게 유지되면서 Heisenberg-limited scaling을 달성함을 증명한다. 이 방법을 multi-mode system으로 효율적으로 확장하기 위해, 기존 simultaneous estimation scheme보다 우수한 statistical efficiency를 제공하는 hierarchical coefficient recovery strategy를 개발한다. 중요한 점은, 우리의 framework가 first-quantized formulation에서의 Hamiltonian coefficient learning에도 자연스럽게 적용되어, 기존 CV 접근법을 넘어서는 적용 범위를 크게 넓힌다는 것이다. 수치 실험은 단일 모드와 다중 모드 비선형 시스템 모두에서 우리 접근법이 예측된 Heisenberg scaling을 달성함을 검증한다.</p>"},{"id":"60752","en":"Improved Distribution Estimation in $\\ell_\\infty$","ko":"$\\ell_\\infty$에서의 개선된 Distribution Estimation","authors":"Doron Cohen, Aryeh Kontorovich, Yonatan Livshitz","pos":"#4622","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=wwqrH4mwGq","abs":"We present improved bounds for estimating discrete probability distributions under the $\\ell_{\\infty}$ norm. These include minimax bounds in expectation and high-probability tail bounds. We resolve some of the open questions posed in Kontorovich and Painsky (JMLR, 2025) --- including a fully empirical version of the tightest risk bound they presented and identifying the form of the worst-case extremal distribution. Encouraging empirical results are reported as well.","absKo":"우리는 $\\ell_{\\infty}$ norm 하에서 discrete probability distribution을 추정하기 위한 개선된 bounds를 제시한다. 여기에는 기대값에 대한 minimax bound와 high-probability tail bound가 포함된다. 우리는 Kontorovich와 Painsky(JMLR, 2025)가 제기한 일부 open question을 해결한다. 여기에는 그들이 제시한 가장 강한 risk bound의 완전한 empirical version과 worst-case extremal distribution의 형태를 식별하는 것이 포함된다. 또한 고무적인 실험 결과를 보고한다."},{"id":"62915","en":"Learning Gaussian Graphical Models from a Glauber Trajectory Without Mixing","ko":"혼합 없이 Glauber 궤적으로 Gaussian Graphical Model 학습","authors":"Eric Shen, Tony Wu, Mahbod Majid, Ankur Moitra","pos":"#4623","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=bvNGrd4UxO","abs":"We study the task of learning the structure of a $d$-sparse Gaussian graphical model on $n$ variables from a single trajectory of Glauber dynamics. Beyond algorithmic considerations, many applications present temporally correlated observations rather than i.i.d. samples. Moreover, in the classical i.i.d. setting, polynomial-time structure learning from a sublinear in $n$ number of samples is suspected to be computationally hard without additional assumptions on the precision matrix. Motivated in part by this, we design the first polynomial-time algorithm that recovers the conditional-independence graph from a single Glauber trajectory, with a trajectory-length guarantee that does not depend on the mixing time.  Technically, our algorithm has three components. First, we estimate the conditional variances and rescale the trajectory to reduce to the unit-diagonal case, without changing the underlying graph. Second, we design a local edge test that extracts adjacency information from short update windows by isolating pairwise influence. Third, we aggregate these local statistics using a robust median-based estimator, and prove accuracy despite contamination and temporal dependence arising from a single trajectory.","absKo":"우리는 단일 Glauber dynamics trajectory로부터 $n$개 변수에 대한 $d$-sparse Gaussian graphical model의 구조를 학습하는 문제를 연구한다. 알고리즘적 고려를 넘어, 많은 응용에서는 i.i.d. 샘플이 아니라 시간적으로 상관된 관측이 주어진다. 더 나아가 고전적인 i.i.d. 설정에서도, precision matrix에 대한 추가 가정이 없으면 $n$보다 sublinear한 샘플 수로 polynomial-time 구조 학습을 하는 것은 계산적으로 어렵다고 의심되어 왔다. 이러한 점에 일부 동기를 받아, 우리는 mixing time에 의존하지 않는 trajectory-length 보장을 갖는, 단일 Glauber trajectory로부터 conditional-independence graph를 복원하는 최초의 polynomial-time 알고리즘을 설계한다. 기술적으로, 우리의 알고리즘은 세 가지 구성요소를 가진다. 첫째, underlying graph는 바꾸지 않으면서 conditional variance를 추정하고 trajectory를 rescale하여 unit-diagonal case로 환원한다. 둘째, pairwise influence를 분리함으로써 짧은 update window에서 adjacency 정보를 추출하는 local edge test를 설계한다. 셋째, 이러한 local statistic을 robust한 median-based estimator로 집계하고, 단일 trajectory에서 비롯되는 contamination과 temporal dependence가 존재하더라도 정확도를 증명한다."},{"id":"64667","en":"Optimal Statistical Guarantees for Diffusion Models on Low-Dimensional, Multi-Modal Data","ko":"저차원 멀티모달 데이터에서 Diffusion Model을 위한 최적 통계적 보장","authors":"Jingda Wu, Changxiao Cai","pos":"#4624","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=L5JTAPUdbQ","abs":"Score-based diffusion models have demonstrated remarkable empirical success in learning high-dimensional distributions, particularly those exhibiting low-dimensional and multi-modal structures. However, theoretical understanding of their statistical efficiency remains limited. Existing theories typically rely on strong regularity assumptions, such as uniformly bounded densities or globally smooth score functions, which fail to capture such intrinsic structures. In this work, we study the sample complexity of diffusion models in learning distributions supported on a union of low-dimensional subspaces. Assuming that data within each subspace follows a subgaussian distribution, we show that diffusion models require at most $\\widetilde{O}(\\varepsilon^{-k \\vee 2})$ samples to achieve $\\varepsilon$ error in 1-Wasserstein distance, where $k$ is the intrinsic dimension. This near-optimal rate depends only on the intrinsic dimension and significantly improves upon prior works that suffer from the curse of dimensionality. Notably, our analysis applies to a broad collection of distributions without requiring smoothness or log-concavity assumptions. These results provide rigorous evidence for the effectiveness of diffusion models in learning low-dimensional, multi-modal distributions.","absKo":"Score-based diffusion model은 특히 low-dimensional 및 multi-modal structure를 보이는 고차원 분포를 학습하는 데서 놀라운 경험적 성공을 보여왔다. 그러나 이들의 통계적 효율성에 대한 이론적 이해는 여전히 제한적이다. 기존 이론은 일반적으로 균일하게 bounded된 density나 전역적으로 smooth한 score function과 같은 강한 regularity assumption에 의존하는데, 이는 이러한 intrinsic structure를 포착하지 못한다. 본 연구에서는 low-dimensional subspace들의 합집합에 지지되는 분포를 학습하는 diffusion model의 sample complexity를 연구한다. 각 subspace 내부의 데이터가 subgaussian 분포를 따른다고 가정하면, diffusion model은 1-Wasserstein distance에서 $\\varepsilon$ 오차를 달성하기 위해 최대 $\\widetilde{O}(\\varepsilon^{-k \\vee 2})$개의 sample만 필요함을 보인다. 여기서 $k$는 intrinsic dimension이다. 이 거의 최적에 가까운 rate는 intrinsic dimension에만 의존하며, dimensionality curse에 시달리는 기존 연구를 크게 개선한다. 특히 본 분석은 smoothness나 log-concavity 가정을 요구하지 않고도 광범위한 분포에 적용된다. 이러한 결과는 low-dimensional multi-modal 분포를 학습하는 데 있어 diffusion model의 효과에 대한 엄밀한 근거를 제공한다.</p>"},{"id":"62572","en":"Provable Bounds for the Learnability of Sample-Compressible Families from Noisy Samples","ko":"노이즈 샘플로부터 noise-compressible family의 학습 가능성에 대한 provable bounds","authors":"Arefe Boushehrian, Amir Najafi","pos":"#4625","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=fRonOqrKWT","abs":"Learning distribution families over $\\mathbb{R}^d$ is a fundamental problem in unsupervised learning and statistics. A central question in this setting is whether a given family of distributions possesses sufficient structure to be (at least) information-theoretically learnable and, if so, to characterize its sample complexity. In 2018, Ashtiani et al. (2018) reformulated sample compressibility as a structural property of distribution classes, proving that it guarantees PAC-learnability. This discovery subsequently enabled a series of recent advancements in deriving nearly tight sample complexity bounds for various high-dimensional open problems. It has been further conjectured that the converse also holds: every learnable class admits a sample compression scheme, making the two notions to be equivalent. In this work, we establish that sample compressible families remain learnable even from perturbed samples, subject to a set of minimax-necessary and sufficient conditions. In particular, we assume samples are corrupted by an additive independent noise model, and theoretically derive sample complexity bounds for general sample compressible classes in arbitrary dimensions with respect to both $\\ell_2$-norm and total variation distance.","absKo":"분포족을 $\\mathbb{R}^d$ 위에서 학습하는 것은 unsupervised learning과 statistics의 근본 문제다. 이 설정의 핵심 질문은 주어진 분포족이 적어도 information-theoretically learnable 할 만큼 충분한 구조를 가지는지, 그리고 그렇다면 sample complexity를 어떻게 특징지을 수 있는지이다. 2018년 Ashtiani et al. (2018)은 sample compressibility를 분포 클래스의 구조적 성질로 재정식화하여, 이것이 PAC-learnability를 보장함을 증명했다. 이 발견은 이후 다양한 고차원 open problem에 대해 거의 tight한 sample complexity bound를 도출하는 최근의 일련의 발전을 가능하게 했다. 또한 역도 성립한다는 추측도 제기되었다: 모든 learnable class는 sample compression scheme을 가지며, 두 개념은 동치라는 것이다. 본 연구에서는 sample compressible family가 perturb된 sample로부터도 여전히 학습 가능함을, minimax에 대해 필요충분한 조건 집합 하에서 확립한다. 특히 우리는 sample이 additive independent noise model로 오염된다고 가정하고, 임의 차원에서 일반 sample compressible class에 대한 sample complexity bound를 $\\ell_2$-norm과 total variation distance 모두에 대해 이론적으로 도출한다."},{"id":"62422","en":"Mind the Gap: Catching Hallucinations via Evidence Drop on the Reasoning Manifold","ko":"갭을 메우다: Reasoning Manifold에서 Evidence Drop을 통한 Hallucination 탐지","authors":"QunJie Chen, Yufei Chen, Xiaodong Yue, Linye Li","pos":"#3817","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=gllCfOG1Gt","abs":"<p>Large Language Models (LLMs) show strong reasoning abilities, yet their reliability is hindered by hallucinations, where fluent reasoning becomes factually or logically incorrect. Most existing uncertainty-based detectors rely on sequence-level averaging, which ignores the step-wise dynamics of reasoning and often misclassifies hard-but-correct or easy-but-wrong samples. We propose a dynamic perspective that models reasoning as a trajectory on a latent \\emph{Evidence Manifold}, where each step is supported by local evidence. Hallucinations are characterized as \\emph{Evidence Drops}, i.e., sudden declines in local evidence support that indicate topological deviations from this manifold. Based on this insight, we design a training-free and model-agnostic detector that identifies hallucinations via the worst-case Evidence Drop and enables step-level error localization. Experiments on GSM8K, MATH, and ProcessBench show consistent improvements over sequence-level uncertainty baselines in selective accuracy and risk–coverage trade-offs.</p>","absKo":"<p>Large Language Models (LLMs)은 강한 reasoning 능력을 보이지만, 유창한 reasoning이 사실적으로 또는 논리적으로 잘못되는 hallucination 때문에 신뢰성이 저해된다. 기존의 대부분 uncertainty-based detector는 sequence-level averaging에 의존하여 reasoning의 step-wise dynamics를 무시하고, 어려우나 정답인 샘플이나 쉬우나 오답인 샘플을 자주 잘못 분류한다. 우리는 reasoning을 latent \\emph{Evidence Manifold} 위의 trajectory로 모델링하는 동적 관점을 제안하며, 각 step은 local evidence에 의해 지지된다. Hallucination은 \\emph{Evidence Drop}, 즉 이 manifold에 대한 topological deviation을 시사하는 local evidence support의 급격한 감소로 특징지어진다. 이러한 통찰을 바탕으로, 우리는 worst-case Evidence Drop을 통해 hallucination을 식별하고 step-level error localization을 가능하게 하는 training-free이며 model-agnostic한 detector를 설계한다. GSM8K, MATH, ProcessBench에서의 실험은 selective accuracy와 risk–coverage trade-off 모두에서 sequence-level uncertainty baseline 대비 일관된 개선을 보여준다.</p>"},{"id":"65543","en":"Optimal Regret for Policy Optimization in Contextual Bandits","ko":"Contextual Bandit에서 정책 최적화를 위한 최적 후회","authors":"Orin Levy, Yishay Mansour","pos":"#4500","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=CXsD6Ygc8e","abs":"We present the first high-probability optimal regret bound for a policy optimization technique applied to the problem of stochastic contextual multi-armed bandit (CMAB) with general offline function approximation. Our algorithm is both efficient and achieves an optimal regret bound of $\\widetilde{O}(\\sqrt{ K|\\mathcal{A}|\\log|\\mathcal{F}|})$, where $K$ is the number of rounds, $\\mathcal{A}$ is the set of arms, and $\\mathcal{F}$ is the function class used to approximate the losses. Our results bridge the gap between theory and practice, demonstrating that the widely used policy optimization methods for the contextual bandit problem can achieve a rigorously-proved optimal regret bound.  We support our theoretical results with an empirical evaluation of our algorithm."}];window.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent("papers-loaded",{detail:"68685"}));